INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1, 1, 1, 1, '2015-08-20', 'I have a Keurig at home and have enjoyed it for the past 3 years I am very regretful that I bought this machine. I have a Keurig at home and have enjoyed it for the past 3 years. However, I purchased this machine for my daughter to take to college. My machine at home I use bottled water and other brands of K-Cups in my machine and have had no problems. I had to contact customer service immediately when setting up this machine in my daughters dorm room this week. I cannot use bottled water and I cannot use any other brand of K-Cups or pods but the Keurig brand in this machine due to it has a digital eye that reads the ink on the Keurig foil label on the K-Cups. I would have taken the machine back right then but I was 2 hours away from home and left the receipt at home. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"  I will also be writing a letter to the company.'),
(2, 2, 1, 3, '2015-08-01', 'Three Stars The knobs are clumsy to uselook at them closely in the pic before buying.'),
(3, 3, 1, 3, '2015-08-23', 'Cooks well but the buttons are obnoxiously loud Every time you press a button, the beep it gives off is the same volume as the alarm beep. No exaggeration.  I been woken by this thing many times. When was the last time you wanted to make toast in the middle of the night and thought, \"I\'d like a piece of toast, but I\'ll probably wake up the house just by pressing a few buttons?\" Other than that it does cook well.'),
(4, 4, 1, 1, '2015-05-23', 'to bad \" But we will sell you a new one Don\'t Do It !!!!!!! Lower coils cracked and caught fire. Was replaced under warranty. Second one worked for 2 months and the lower coils quit all together. They wanted a receipt and I told them I did not get one with the warranty replacement. They said \" so sorry, to bad \" But we will sell you a new one. In the first e-mails they said we are sending a new one to you. They then sent another e-mail with the paragraph about sending a new one,\" GONE \" from their e-mail. How ever I still have mine. That shows just how customer oriented they really are and how hurting they really are. SAD!!!!!! Stay clear from Cuisinart. Unfortunately I own tons of their products. Never again.'),
(5, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-06', 'Five Stars This item was also given as a gift and is being used daily ;'),
(6, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-08', 'I dont like calling them toaster ovens I dont like calling them toaster ovens, though! Kind of crazy to think about and actually say out loud: Regular toasters do a quicker job of toasting bread. So, if all you need to toast is bread, go get yourself a toaster with the highest wattage that you can afford, and forget this toaster oven. I think a lot of people are disappointed with their toaster ovens because they dont do a great job of toasting bread_..Get this oven for toasting, broiling, baking other types of food, then use it to toast bread as a secondary, or fallback, duty.'),
(7, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'A better coffee maker than I had previously A better coffee maker than I had previously. The design of the carafe does not allow coffee to pour over the side. The removable water tank allows  for easy cleaning. Overall a nice coffee maker.'),
(8, 6, 1, 3, '2015-09-11', 'Good toaster for the price The first toaster had a short in the cord. The replacement has been trouble free but the toaster is fine. I tend to use the lower settings so not to burn the toast. The toast comes out a little uneven.'),
(9, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-02', 'Great Toaster for bread and small frozen foods This Toaster Oven is a great addition to my kitchen. Its a great size, not too big, not too small.  I made some grilled cheese sandwiches with it and they came out perfect. It\'s also good for heating up frozen waffles and other small items. Easy to clean as well'),
(10, 7, 3, 4, '2015-10-15', 'When I first set it up I had bought at the same time senceo pods..this did not work at all.. the water poured through and looked like it had not even hit the pod at all. As far as K-cups yes..But pods NO! Unless someone could give me some suggestions?'),
(11, 8, 1, 5, '2014-01-22', 'Why would you want more from a coffee maker? This is super basic...and super resilient.  I am always scratching my head at folks who will spend hundreds of dollars...FOR A COFFEE MAKER!  Look, this makes great coffee. No, it doesn\'t do \"one cups\" (I suppose you can) and you don\'t have to pay $2.50 for a stupid plastic gizmo that gives you precisely ONE CUP...good lord, have we come to this?  Just make some coffee and pour the rest down the drain.  Anyway, this is a work horse and just keeps on going.  Take that, Kuerig.'),
(12, 2, 1, 2, '2015-05-22', 'Cheap construction; runs hot Very cheap construction. A lot more heat escapes it than a lot of other toasters. There\'s a lot of weird redundancy in the dials.'),
(13, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-12', 'Nice for rushed mornings! I am testing and reviewing this Keurig. I had never really been interested in Keurig\'s prior because I usually get locally roasted coffee beans that I use in my regular coffee maker. In testing this Keurig out I have enjoyed the simplicity of it. It is nice to just be able to pop a pod in and brew my morning coffee. The touch screen works great and I like that there is the option for different size cups and a strong brew. There are a couple things that I don\'t like so much. Since I like local coffee it would be nice if I could use the \"make-your-own-pods\", but it will only brew Keurig brand pods. The second thing is, I usually drink larger cups of coffee and it only brews up to 10oz. I understand the pods don\'t hold that much coffee but instead of brewing two pods or the same one twice it would be nice to at least still have the option to brew up to 12 oz. Overall, I have enjoyed this Keurig. It\'s nice for rushed mornings when I don\'t have time to grind coffee beans and make a pot of coffee. I also don\'t like you can\'t fit normal \"to go\" cups under it. I think I will always use my normal coffee maker most often and use the Keurig for mornings I\'m running behind.'),
(14, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-04', 'Best coffee maker I\'ve had so far. This coffee maker exceeded our expectations. The coffee is actually hot from the first to the last cup and the last cup is as good as the first. The design also makes it easy to operate and program for the next morning. I would recommend this coffee maker to everyone who loves coffee.'),
(15, 3, 1, 4, '2015-01-29', 'cooks and bakes perfectly! From broiled chicken, to baked salmon, pizza, cupcakes, cookies and even cakes, this convection oven makes everything perfect. It\'s so easy to use and display is easy to follow. It\'s the perfect size for small families, or independent living young people like me.'),
(16, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-22', 'Four Stars I am very satisfied with this toaster.  I suits my needs'),
(17, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-21', 'Four Stars Does what I need!!'),
(18, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-30', 'Fast and toasts on both sides of the bread. Looked for a long time before I finally decided to buy this one.  So far, all I\'ve used is the toast feature but it toasts well on both sides and does so quickly.  My only problem is trying to not burn it.  My old toaster oven would take forever to toast bread.  If you do buy this model, use a lighter setting on the toast unless you like it really dark.  It\'s big enough to toast 4 slices of bread.  I like that the crumb tray slides out for cleaning.  The handles stays cool.  A great toaster oven especially for the money.  Very happy with my purchase.'),
(19, 5, 1, 1, '2014-08-31', 'The Coffeemaker stopped working after only 2 months. No ... The Coffeemaker stopped working after only 2 months.  No information on how to return it after the 2 month limit.'),
(20, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-01', 'Amazingly cheap yet sturdy.. I use this every day: it\'s strong enough to grind up a couple of ice cubes, kefir, protein powder, and frozen fruit into a smoothie in seconds. Amazingly cheap yet sturdy... this is my backup, but my original is still going strong after more than two years.'),
(21, 11, 1, 3, '2014-08-22', 'It looks nice on my counter and I like the size This item was shipped promptly and was well packaged. That being said I am having problems setting the temperature so that my bread gets toasted and not burned. Either it\'s too lightly toasted or it\'s burned. It looks nice on my counter and I like the size, it doesn\'t take up too much space. NOW IF I COULD ONLY GET IT TO WORK PROPERLY.'),
(22, 2, 1, 3, '2016-03-18', 'Hard to dial in. To get to toaster mode, you have to put on magnifying glasses to see the markings. And if you turn the toast knob more than 1/4 the way around, it burns the toast.I wonder what the rest of the dial is for, incineration?'),
(23, 2, 1, 4, '2015-09-04', 'Four Stars Just wished it looked better, but for $30 what can you expect?'),
(24, 3, 1, 2, '2015-11-24', 'Two Stars I don\'t use it all the time and have to read the instructions every time. Not very user friendly.'),
(25, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-06', 'Good toaster Works good.  Fits on our small counter by the stove.'),
(26, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-18', 'This is our second. We pounded our first into ... This is our second. We pounded our first into the ground. After 5 years, it had had enough. Bought another without hesitation and this gets used every day as well!'),
(27, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'I love my Keurig 2.0!! I had the Keurig platinum for a few years and decided to upgrade to the newer model. My favorite part of the Keurig 2.0 is the touch screen display and the option to make a strong cup of coffee even with a light roast. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review'),
(28, 5, 1, 2, '2015-02-17', 'A simple stove top coffeemaker works better and lasts This quit working.  I wish I had my money back.  A simple stove top coffeemaker works better and lasts.'),
(29, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-30', 'Not as easy to use as the older model with knobs. Not as easy to use as the older model with knobs.'),
(30, 5, 1, 1, '2015-04-17', 'I want my coffee without grounds. For unknown reasons it worked as it should for a few months. Since then I get coffee grounds with my coffee. I have used the same measure of Melitta Columbian for many years and have tried Bunn and grocery store filters. The machine has been cleaned.  The pot is carefully placed. I usually use 11 cups of water because 12 cups invariably produces lots of grounds in the carafe.'),
(31, 9, 1, 1, '2016-08-29', 'One Star To be short, precise and to the point, IT LEAKS.'),
(32, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-10', 'Five Stars Love it. Keeps the coffee hot with out the burnt taste of most coffee makers.'),
(33, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-18', 'Good solid purchase Been a great purchase. I make a 20 oz cup for myself & the 2-4 cup setting makes a solid cup of Joe.'),
(34, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-14', 'Bought this for my husband for Christmas and he LOVES it!! He\'s the only one that drinks coffee or tea in the family, so it\'s perfect for him, plus the size fits my counter space (a BIG plus for me!) I would highly recommend it..:-)'),
(35, 5, 1, 4, '2015-07-11', 'The machine makes good coffee and it is nice and hot The machine makes good coffee and it is nice and hot.  4 stars because I don\'t like the lid on the pot.  You cannot take it off which makes it a little more difficult to clean the pot. The lid also comes open while pouring coffee allowing steam to heat up your hand.  There is also a small thermometer next to the light; what is that for?  Cosmetics?  I could understand it being there if it had a function, but I haven\'t seen one.'),
(36, 4, 1, 2, '2015-04-22', 'good feature set and almost trouble free Love/Hate.  Unit is great- operates as advertised, good feature set and almost trouble free... Almost that is, until the heater element fails and you have to deal with Cuisinart\'s customer service.  Be aware that they will certainly honor their warranty, but somewhat at your expense.  As documented elsewhere, shipping of the old unit back to them and the cost of shipping a new unit to you is on your nickel.  So, the question is, is it worth paying $40 to get a unit with known issues?  If not for the reliability and customer service issues, this would be a 5 star review.'),
(37, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-25', 'Five Stars great product and wonderful price.'),
(38, 11, 1, 2, '2014-04-14', 'Not as large as listed Disappointed.  No way a 9\" pizza will fit. Body/shell takes up a lot of space and interior is small compared to exterior size.'),
(39, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'Five Stars Easy to use, good for bringing it to work.'),
(40, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-13', 'Five Stars Love this coffeemaker! It brews wonderful coffee and it\'s not noisy.'),
(41, 9, 1, 1, '2016-06-15', 'New or Pre-owned?? Worst packaging ever.  Came in original package and without instructions and was spotty. Pre-owned? Paid for a new one! Disappointed!'),
(42, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Five Stars Working every day. No problems.'),
(43, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-04', 'Perfect for Solder Oven Made a Solder Oven out of this appliance. Works perfectly.'),
(44, 6, 1, 4, '2016-12-28', 'Four Stars We really like this toaster. It looks nice on the counter and works perfectly.'),
(45, 7, 3, 3, '2014-03-20', 'Brews well, but not hot enough for coffee for me. Worked great for iced teas, and was perfect temp for hot chocolate for my son. Will return and get a Keurig because of water temp.'),
(46, 8, 1, 5, '2014-10-26', 'Great Little Coffee Maker Love this coffee pot; perfect for smaller households. We have worn out two others over the years.'),
(47, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Great Machine I love this machine so much more than my off brand. I found that the functions were spot on for my personal tastes, and it makes a good cup of coffee. I like the reservoir which makes it easier to brew one cup after another, and I love that I have the option to brew a small pot as well! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(48, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-17', 'Good everyday toaster... works as needed. compact and functional. Makes Yummy bagels..crisp and fast.'),
(49, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Five Stars Great coffee'),
(50, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-24', 'Great machine Straightforward, easy to use coffee maker that has a few features you\'ll love (programmable percolation and adjustable burner temperature) but not over-engineered.  Makes great coffee.'),
(51, 12, 1, 5, '2014-05-27', 'It\'s a toaster Yes, it works perfectly. I have a small kitchen and I love that it has two functions without taking up a lot of space. Small footprint, many uses, clean and modern lines, reliable, need I say more?'),
(52, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-16', 'Love it - now i dont need to use my ... Love it - now i dont need to use my large over when i need to put in 2 garlic breads'),
(53, 4, 1, 4, '2015-11-10', 'Toasts evenly for bread and bagels. I included a ... Toasts evenly for bread and bagels.  I included a picture so you can see how even the toasting is.  You are welcome.'),
(54, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'Five Stars Perfect!'),
(55, 2, 1, 1, '2015-04-15', 'If I could give it a zero...I would.  This is my second oven, sent first back for the same reason. Heating element Keeps turning off..this is with a single slice of toast in the oven.'),
(56, 6, 1, 4, '2016-04-04', 'Four Stars it works. \'nuff said.'),
(57, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', '96 year old loves it Great product'),
(58, 12, 1, 5, '2016-03-08', 'Perfect for my needs I try to keep my countertop clear of clutter so was looking for a toaster oven that would also function as a toaster. I\'ve had this toaster oven for over a year now and find that it is perfect for my needs. It is nice to be able to keep this appliance out on the counter. The toast function works just as a regular toaster does. It fits a regular sized bagel or some thickly sliced bread. The oven portion is a bit shallow, so if your garlic bread is really thick, you will end up burning the top or not even able to close the door. I haven\'t really had too much of a problem with the oven based on my simple needs. It roasts a bunch of asparagus with no problem and in no time. Anything larger I use my gas stove. I find this machine an asset to my kitchen.'),
(59, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'Perfect for the counter and for little ones to bake ... Sleek and not too big. Perfect for the counter and for little ones to bake with.'),
(60, 8, 1, 4, '2014-09-30', 'Perfect for occasional coffee drinkers Not the greatest coffee maker you\'ll find, but it gets the job done. Needs plenty of run-throughs to get that plastic/dusty smell out of it.'),
(61, 2, 1, 2, '2015-09-10', 'Functional BUT... It does what I need it to do: toasts bread and warms things up.  BUT the darn thing won\'t heat past 350. It\'s supposed to heat to 450. Can\'t get it there no matter how long I let it heat.'),
(62, 9, 1, 4, '2016-05-17', 'Four Stars Great coffee pot, coffe is really hot and the fuel gage is awesome'),
(63, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-30', 'Five Stars Good Product'),
(64, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-27', 'Five Stars Love it.'),
(65, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-05', 'Easy, functional, perfect! I have to say that I rarely give 5 star ratings to any product, however this Hamilton Beach coffee maker has been excellent since I first purchased it months ago.  I am a daily coffee drinker, usually having 2-3 cups every morning, and I wanted something that not only had automatic brew setting but looked good as well as being easy to use and clean.  This Hamilton Beach looks great, especially with the stainless steel front and blue digital display.  The automatic brew is easy to setup and works flawlessly each morning, and the digital display along with option buttons on either side allow make it super user friendly.  The detachable water container in the back is a great feature too, as I don\'t have to spill water everywhere trying to funnel it into the top of a traditional maker, I just take the container to the sink, fill it with water, attach it back, and it\'s all done.  I also am happy with how easy it is to clean!  I guess the most important part is the coffee it brews, and from my experience it\'s been good, hot and flavorful.  I\'ve used Mr. Coffee and Kuerig and the Hamilton Beach holds up to those in terms of coffee taste/temperature with no problem.'),
(66, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-21', 'Five Stars Perfect for a single person who needs 32 oz of coffee to start their day.'),
(67, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(68, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-23', 'Super buy. Love it Love this coffee pot. Just wonderful.'),
(69, 10, 1, 3, '2015-04-21', 'While the size is nice, it\'s nit a heavy duty blender but it\'s ... While the size is nice, it\'s nit a heavy duty blender but it\'s good for quick smoothies that mix quick. There was an awful smell that radiated the first few times I used it. The cup is a nice portable size.'),
(70, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-22', 'Four Stars Produce a very tasteful fruit shake, really helps to my daily diet.'),
(71, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-15', 'Satisfaction very satisfied with this product'),
(72, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker..Keeps me sane most days!!.'),
(73, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-16', 'is a great value and was received sooner than anticipated The product was as described, is a great value and was received sooner than anticipated. We are very happy with this purchase.'),
(74, 5, 1, 2, '2016-04-24', 'Did not meet our needs. Ended up buying a different brand in a local store.'),
(75, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-19', 'Great toaster...great price... Does a great job have toasted both sides equally and as expected.  Very sturdy and very happy...'),
(76, 6, 1, 4, '2014-07-20', 'Toasts fine It toasts the bread, bagels, premade waffles. I don\'t eat any of this stuff, generally, but there have been no complaints from the fam about unevenness, burning, or any of the other woes some reviewers complained of. It just seems like a toaster, basically.'),
(77, 6, 1, 1, '2015-10-03', 'Such poor quality. It was to replace a twenty year ... Returned this toaster.  Such poor quality.  It was to replace a twenty year old Cuisinart toaster.  Happily the twenty year old seems to have taken on a second life, and is performing admirably again. This CPT-122 has very small slots for the bread, and I found that most bread would not fit in the slots without trimming.  Poor design and quality.'),
(78, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-03', 'Five Stars Makes really great smoothies'),
(79, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-10', 'Cuisinart CPT-122 2 Slice Toaster It\'s a basic toaster and that\'s what I was looking for. It works well, takes up very little room on my counter top, and it looks good.'),
(80, 5, 1, 2, '2016-03-27', 'The spout of the coffee pot is so narrow it ... The spout of the coffee pot is so narrow it spills water every time you fill the reservoir to make a new pot.  And almost every time pouring a cup.  Definitely not for making coffee for a group of people every day.'),
(81, 11, 1, 1, '2014-08-21', 'This toaster oven is terrible! No matter what setting you put it on This toaster oven is terrible! No matter what setting you put it on, it burns the toast every time! It\'s a safety hazard!'),
(82, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-21', 'Five Stars Excellent'),
(83, 2, 1, 1, '2016-05-16', 'so diappointed I had purchased a toaster from B+D about one month before purchasing this oven. The reason I purchased this was because in less than 2 weeks of using the toaster it stopped working. So, me thinking it was a defect and not B+D I bought this oven. The FIRST time I turned it on to test it, it started smoking uncontrollably inside the mechanics (not inside the oven) and started sparking and I believe almost caught fire. the smell was clearly the smell of electric parts burning. I should have known better, if a simple toaster can last more than a couple weeks, why would I spend MORE money on a product from the same manufacturer. I hope these products don\'t reflect all Black and decker products as of late because I am getting a trimmer from them and would hate to give up all together.'),
(84, 12, 1, 3, '2016-12-02', 'Ok but Oversized It\'s pretty big. The top  toaster only fits 3 slices of English muffin so I have to make the 4th slice separately after the first 3 halves are done - pretty annoying .'),
(85, 5, 1, 4, '2014-11-14', 'Four Stars as expected'),
(86, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-05', 'I love this machine!! Perfect for an on the go person who doesn\'t want to spend a ton on a kurig. I can use my favorite ground coffee or pick one of many k cups.'),
(87, 8, 1, 1, '2016-07-23', 'Taste bad!!! Terrible plastic or chlorine taste and smell.  I have washed it out with soap. Used lemon inside. Run vinegar through several times. Even put outside in sun for a day- to \"air out\". Still just as bad. Forget this one!.'),
(88, 5, 1, 2, '2015-01-06', 'Dissapointed. Cheaply made and the coffee tastes awful. I was very disappointed with this product. I purchased it for my wife to replace out old Hamilton Beach machine (which we were very happy with). After reading all the good reviews I was pretty excited to receive it. However, upon unpacking it, I discovered it\'s really very poorly made. Most of it is cheap plastic, not even well cast enough for all the lines to fit together properly. The \'stainless steel\' portion certainly doesn\'t look or feel like stainless steel, it looks and feels like plastic made to look like stainless steel. The worst part is the carafe, I think it\'s glass but it feels very light, thin and fragile and I don\'t have any confidence that it won\'t shatter with the slightest bump. The whole thing feels like it came from some low end foreign production line. On the plus side, it does see very easy to fill and clean. This is the reason I bought it as my wife has fibromyalgia and easy access and maintenance is a priority for us. So, putting my disappointment with the manufacture standards aside, I figured as long as it makes a decent cup of coffee we\'d live with it. But no matter what ratios of coffee:water we put in, it always seems to come out bitter. We\'re not coffee snobs - we just use regular pre-ground Folgers, which tasted great through the other machine. If I can figure out how to get a palatable cup out of this I\'ll come back here and edit my review. But if not, this is going back to the vendor pretty soon.'),
(89, 8, 1, 1, '2016-03-19', 'One Star Handle fell off while unpacking.'),
(90, 5, 1, 1, '2014-08-19', 'Terrible product Made great coffee but it completely crapped out and died on me in less than a year.'),
(91, 3, 1, 3, '2016-10-08', 'Top and door gets way too hot. Top and door front gets very hot. It is a little hard to figure out how to operate it. It takes up more room than I thought it would.  I had to re-arrange every -thing on my kitchen counter because the top gets so hot.  So now it is not under any overhead cabinet.  I am not totally happy with it.  I wish I had paid more attention to the dimensions.  Have used it several time now, and I suppose I will get used to it, but my little Black and Decker I loved.  I was so sorry it died.'),
(92, 11, 1, 3, '2015-07-22', 'This toaster oven worked perfectly. It was simply too ... This toaster oven worked perfectly.  It was simply too small.  It was difficult to fit 4 pieces of bread in to make toast.'),
(93, 6, 1, 4, '2015-07-07', 'Great Toaster Great toaster. It\'s very easy to use and toasts perfectly and fastly. It\'s a great value and we\'re very happy with the product.'),
(94, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Works great. The motor starts to smell after some use Works great.  The motor starts to smell after some use.  I am not sure if that means it will die soon, but it has been working well.  I make smoothies mostly with it.'),
(95, 8, 1, 2, '2014-09-07', 'Never again.  : I\'ve had two of these fail on me in as many years.  Both died around the 8-10 month mark.  These are cheap and a short life-span is to be expected, but to have them fail in less than a year is somewhat irritating. They start off working well, then one day the heating element stops heating. Given that they can be purchased for under twenty dollars, it\'s not really cost-effective to send it back for a replacement under warranty.'),
(96, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-11', 'Five Stars Beautiful...it is perfect...!.'),
(97, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-08', 'LOVE IT They did a fantastic job delivering it in a timely manner, and the product looks great! Can\'t wait to use it!'),
(98, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-16', 'Five Stars Works great and easy to clean and fill.'),
(99, 10, 1, 3, '2015-10-14', 'Not what i expected Item is advertised as great for smoothies and that is just about all it can do. I was hoping for a bit more and I guess that is my fault for wistful thinking. It is small and compact making it easy to leave on the counter. Only holds about 400 ml and only has one speed. Again, ideal for smoothies and shakes. Nothing more.'),
(100, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-22', 'This coffee maker is inexpensive and brews great coffee. We wanted a coffee maker that brewed ... This coffee maker is inexpensive and brews great coffee. We wanted a coffee maker that brewed bold coffee and this one does the trick nicely. We have tried a metal screen filter and of course the paper filters and prefer the paper filters as they seem to encourage a stronger flavor. This machine is easy to use and in few weeks we\'ve had it has not had one hiccup; it brews our coffee on schedule per the timer each morning. Each 12 cup brew cycle takes about 10 minutes but it\'s worth it.'),
(101, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-05', 'Delicious Coffee every time with this great Coffee Maker! I love the Hamilton Beach 46201 12 Cup Digital Coffeemaker, Stainless Steel coffee maker. It has an awesome design that goes along with any type of kitchen. The stainless steel look really makes it pop out when it sits on your kitchen counter. To make coffee, you follow a few simple steps. Fill out the removable water container from the back of the unit and fill it up with water, then replace back onto the unit. This is a great feature because you dont have to fill out a cup or bring a pot of water to the unit. It really helps to not make a mess. In the front of the unit, there is a compartment that opens up which allows you to place the filter and coffee. Finally, make sure you have a clean and empty pot and click on the Start button. Within a few minutes, you will be enjoying an amazing cup of coffee. At the end of the day, you get a great looking unit, not very noisy and very clean for a great price.'),
(102, 9, 1, 1, '2016-01-27', 'One Star Coffee maker is great. Amazon decide to cut the price 65% 3 days after I bought it'),
(103, 6, 1, 1, '2016-03-20', 'Don\'t be fooled, this toaster doesn\'t have a \"Bagel\" setting I bought this toaster expecting the quality expected from Cuisinart, I was disappointed and returned the unit. The unit advertises a Bagel function but it doesn\'t perform as such. Every other toaster I have ever owned, including a Cuisinart, had a Bagel function that toasted one side of the bagel only, this bagel function add a few seconds to the toasting time while toasting both sides. This false function is useless as you can achieve the same thing by turning up the setting dial.'),
(104, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-21', 'Five Stars Have enjoyed this toaster oven.  Good size for our counter.  Easy-to-use controls.  It is used a lot.'),
(105, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-12', 'size and the touch screen is awesome. It\'s much quieter than the older one that ... I\'m that person who do not live without coffee. This coffee maker is really modern, the design, colors, size and the touch screen is awesome. It\'s much quieter than the older one that I used to own. It doesn\'t wake up the whole house in the mornings. Also, you can choose four different pour options 4oz, 6oz, 8oz and 10oz. I\'m so amazed with my new best friend!!! I strongly recommend it!! I got this coffee maker for testing purpose!'),
(106, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-03', 'One of the best gifts I ever gave my daughter One of the best gifts I ever gave my daughter. It\'s used every day, 1-3 times. Easy to use. Worth every cent.'),
(107, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-06', 'Gets the job done! Simple coffee maker perfect for small quantities of coffee.'),
(108, 5, 1, 3, '2014-08-29', 'It is easy to program It does not pour clean.  It makes a huge mess when filling the tank, and also when pouring the first few cups.  It is easy to program, and does get and stay exceptionally hot. Also, has auto shut-off... which is nice.  I just wish it poured better.'),
(109, 6, 1, 1, '2014-01-27', 'I was disappointed in the Cuisinart toaster. The LED feature did not work on the toaster. It didn\'t toast even, one side would be darker than the other.'),
(110, 2, 1, 1, '2015-03-29', 'Buy this if you want to burn your house down for the insurance money. All I can say is wow, how could anybody like this toaster. I suppose if you use it as a small oven instead of as a toaster, maybe. This has the most basic design flaw possible. The timer knob is a 30-minute timer. You toast bread for what, 3 minutes? You have to -- by hand -- turn the knob like precisely 1/4 inch for it to make toast. And 1/16 of an inch wrong in either direction results in either completely un-toasted bread or flames. Yes, flames. I have had toast on fire in this thing 4 times. Like completely on fire, trying to find a pair of tongs and get it to the sink. For the life of me I can\'t figure out why they would design it this way. Nor can I figure out how anybody who ever tried to toast a piece of bread in this thing would give it more than 1 star.'),
(111, 6, 1, 2, '2014-11-18', 'I wouldn\'t recommend it it does smell like burned plastic, I don\'t know what I was thinking when I got it... also it toasts on one side and very lightly. I like my bread bit more toasted that that, and possibly heated on both sides. Not happy at all but it\'s kinda of a hassle to return it now .. I guess I am giving it 2 starts instead of 1 bc it wasn\'t too expensive, but still add a few extra $$ and get a non plastic one.'),
(112, 5, 1, 2, '2014-12-08', 'Only lasted 1 year After a year of daily use the internal carafe began leaking.. Boo! I really loved this coffee pot!!'),
(113, 7, 3, 4, '2014-01-21', 'My only complaint is that the mug holder doesn\'t allow for the majority of my mugs to fit under the spout, so I have to remove it and hold the cup up near the spout to avoid splattering. Other than that, it works great!'),
(114, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Great Toaster Oven for the money! Great toaster oven.  I have fixed chicken and it is great not having the house heat up just for twenty minutes of cooking.  To reheat pizza, don\'t use the microwave - yuck!  Lightly spray Pam on a piece of foil and place pizza on foil (do not cover) in toaster oven on the tray at 400 for about 8 minutes.  I love that it remembers my shade of toast for my Toaster Strudel.'),
(115, 7, 3, 3, '2014-01-11', 'the coffeemaker is good for coffee, tea, and apple cider but with hot chocolate it becomes stopped up(run vinegar thru pot to clean chocolate out of pot) I opened chocolate k-cups pour into cup then add water to pot and you have great chocolate. I will buy Hamilton Beach the next time wonderful coffeemaker at a reasonable price.'),
(116, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Five Stars Love it. It\'s small enough to make one serving easy to clean and easy to store'),
(117, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-16', 'Five Stars awesome'),
(118, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-10', 'Five Stars Great transaction, item as described.  Thank you!!'),
(119, 5, 1, 4, '2014-01-05', 'Like it Much better than the Mr Coffees I used to purchase. I really like the fact that the water reservoir comes off to fill.'),
(120, 9, 1, 1, '2016-02-24', 'Don\'t buy this unit it\'s simply JUNK Don\'t waste your money and time buying this JUNK unit. The coffee machine looks good and that\'s it. I purchased this unit brand new in the box not a refurbished or previously returned unit. I followed the instructions carefully and loved it. After the third time of usage I went to get a cup of coffee and it wouldn\'t stop I used several other cups to get all the coffee out. I thought to myself that maybe I did something wrong so I decided to refill it with new grinds and set it up sure enough it poured all overall the place. This is a typical cheap piece of JUNK MADE IN CHUNITO garbage get a real unit you will be very disappointed'),
(121, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-11', 'Five Stars Excellent'),
(122, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-17', 'Works Reliably, Carafe Seam Leaks Every Time We\'ve been using this daily for 10 months.  The brew timer works reliably, and we haven\'t had any problems with the brewing process.  The plastic rim at the top of the carafe that the lid attaches to is not sealed well to the glass, and coffee leaks through the seam onto the counter every time a cup is poured.  After a while we learned to press down on the carafe lid near the front while pouring to prevent leaking.'),
(123, 6, 1, 1, '2015-11-20', 'The bagel setting is just about useless, as it usually burns one side This toaster never toasts a piece of bread the same way twice, even if you don\'t change the settings.  Furthermore, each side of the bread is toasted differently than the other, with one side coming close to being burnt while the other is toasted properly, so you must adjust the settings to compensate for this, and then take the toast out and turn it and then put it back down so no side is over-toasted. The bagel setting is just about useless, as it usually burns one side.  It\'s best just to skip it and keep an eye on the bagels while they are toasting.  The best feature about this toaster is the cancel button, which lets you pop up the toast without using the levers.  I got rid of my old Black & Decker toaster, which we had for 8 years, because it had begun toasting bread the way this brand new Cuisinart does out of the box.  I have used this toaster since April of 2015, and it has not improved with age!  I definitely DO NOT RECOMMEND this toaster!'),
(124, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-07', 'Five Stars lovely, grand!'),
(125, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'This is a great way to prepare coffee and any other hot drink This is a great way to prepare coffee and any other hot drink. The variety of available flavors really makes a great purchase... in if you only want hot water it can do that as well without the hassle of heating on the stove/microwave Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(126, 4, 1, 3, '2015-07-29', 'Glass Door Shattered I absolutely loved this toaster oven......but over time the glass door started to stick and became increasingly harder to open.  Last Saturday I tried to open the door and the glass completely shattered and the handle broke off.'),
(127, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-24', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker! Very easy to use and cleans easily. The brew options are really nice.'),
(128, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-02', 'Five Stars Works great'),
(129, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-26', 'Five Stars This thing works great. Both functions. Retro looks and great function.'),
(130, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-17', 'Best brewer I\'ve owned! I was in need of a new coffee maker, since my little one was making my coffee taste terrible. I decided to bite the bullet and invest in a Keurig Brewer. I decided on the 2.0 k 200 version and I absolutely love it! My coffee tastes amazing everytime. I have not yet used the carafe but I do love the options of multiple K-cup sizes. I have recently bought an ecofill for the 2.0 and use it in between the times that I order more K-cups. Being able to use regular grounds of my own is a nice option to also keep cost down if I am not in a position to buy k-cups. My favorite feature is the 10oz-strong option. I do like getting the most out of each cup and previously with Keurigs I have used made the cup weak if I set it to 10oz. By having the strong option, it brews at a slower rate, really getting all the flavor possible in a large mug. I am very happy with my decision to get a Keurig brewer and recommend it to anyone that loves coffee as much as I do! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(131, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Five Stars This keurig is great and cute and practical! Thanks keurig, for the free kcups for this review! :)'),
(132, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', 'Five Stars Works great and I love the color options!'),
(133, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-24', 'It\'s great. It\'s not too big and doesn\'t take too ... It\'s great. It\'s not too big and doesn\'t take too much space on your counter.  Easy to use and toasts and heats great'),
(134, 9, 1, 1, '2016-03-09', 'At first we loved this coffee maker At first we loved this coffee maker. Major problem and manufacturing flaw: The inside that holds the hot coffee is flawed.  It starts breaking down the plastic liner which comes out when you rinse the holder after use.  You will see pieces of black come out in the sink.  At first I thought it was coffee build up but on further inspection with a flash light we could see how the plastic liner was breaking down.  Also when you touch the plastic that comes out it breaks up into small tiny pieces.  It is also filtered out into your coffee cup.  You will see small little black things in the coffee. Too bad.  We went through two different makers thinking the first one was a problem. But the coffee was great for the time the maker worked before this happened.  Not a good health thing to drink plastic.'),
(135, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-25', 'It does a good job of mixing powder with liquid very This item performs exactly as advertised. It does a good job of mixing powder with liquid very quickly'),
(136, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Good, so close to being great! overall I\'m happy with Keurig 2.0 purchase. it\'s not necessarily enough of an upgrade to warrant buying a new one to replace a fully functional, older style, but since we were due for new one it was definitely a good purchase. we really like that it takes up smaller room on our counter. I do have to out that when you remove the lid to refill the water tank, the condensation spills out onto your countertop! we\'ve learned ways to prevent this from happening just by the way we lift the lid and tap it before we fully remove it from the machine. the fact that the model we purchased didn\'t come with a caraf wasn\'t a huge deal to us since we planned on buying the insulated, stainless steel caraf that can be purchased separately. regarding what other reviewer\'s have said about the limited Kcup selection due to the new required printing on the lids, we haven\'t run into that yet. even the generic market pantry brand from target have the required printing on the top to work 100% in the new Keurig 2.0 unhindered. overall I feel this was a good purchase. it\'s faster, quieter, has the carafe capability when we\'re both ready to drink the same kind of coffee at the same time.  thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review'),
(137, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-17', 'Love It Easy to use and great for single servings.  Easy to store as well.'),
(138, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'This is the best coffee maker I\'ve ever owned This is the best coffee maker I\'ve ever owned. Fully digital to set wake up brewing and adjust how hot the warmer keeps the coffee warm The best part is the removable water bin with a filter. It makes it so easy to fill up and not have to use the pot. I highly recommend this coffee maker.'),
(139, 4, 1, 2, '2016-01-27', 'Cuisinart  toaster oven. The product was much larger than I expected. The dials have no marking on them, so I actually painted with a silver polish the raised ridges on the dials so that I could tell where they pointed. The handle on the door sticks out too far  and is cumbersome. The toasting time seems to take too long even when I adjust the dial. The best feature is the crumb tray. In time I guess I will get used to it.'),
(140, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-06', 'LOVE THIS MACHINE I absolutey love this machine!! I thoughtit only made coffee but it makes my tea as well.  So simple to use and the coffee is perfect each and every time!  Thanks Keurig!'),
(141, 4, 1, 1, '2015-11-27', 'Worked great, but today went haywire dangerously Bought it in 2013.  Worked great, but today went haywire dangerously.  The toaster part and the oven part were turned off, but the upper heating elements were cranking a way, on.  I happened to be in the kitchen doing dishes when I noticed a smell and wondered what was going on. Don\'t buy!'),
(142, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-24', 'Doesn\'t do what it is supposed to I got this for Christmas and I was excited because I wanted something portable to carry my shakes. However, the top doesn\'t fit on the cup; it\'s loose and just sits there. What a disappointment, it\'s the only reason I wanted this.'),
(143, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-16', 'This is the second oven i have bought as a gift and it is loved, loved, loved! This is the second oven I have bought as a gift and it is loved, loved, loved. In fact, its replaced their oven in many cases. The families bake muffins, bread, many of their main meals are now baked in this handy  oven that works like a dream. Unlike a oven it will not heat up your kitchen on hot summer days yet still do all the baking you want, and quickly. You can not beat the price for the quality of this fine Black and Decker oven.'),
(144, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-02', 'Four Stars Great price for this toaster.'),
(145, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-04', 'I really love it! It\'s great for the price NEW UPDATE, 11.08. 2015 : The motor just died after casual use (within a month). I now would say, guys, just pay more and get another one... ******************************************************************************************** I really love it! It\'s great for the price! The smoothie was really smooth. It gets the job done. The only downside would be there is no on and off button. So you need to hold the only button on the machine to make it work, it kinda numb my finger a little if I put too much frozen fruits in it. Overall, I will definitely recommend you all to buy it if you are looking for a single fast serve cheap blender. Ps: the picture is an ACai berries smoothie I just made 10 mins ago. I\'ll keep updating if I found any problem later'),
(146, 4, 1, 2, '2015-11-21', 'Two Stars It was smaller than expected and a bit flimpsy....'),
(147, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-30', 'Love it. Thank you Amazon and seller for great ... Arrived promptly. Works as described. Toast brown on both sides and it toasts bagels.  Love it. Thank you Amazon and seller for great product.'),
(148, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-04', 'A 6 Star product Ok so I dumped my HB Coffee Maker {non carafe type} after replacing it once for leaking and having same problem . Was skeptical about another HB product but reviews made me try it. This is a very well designed Coffee maker. Deserves 6 stars Great features  Non drip carafe , has an insert in carafe to prevent drips Water container lifts out from back approx. 3^ allowing you to leave macine in place and not worry about lifting lid pouring in water. Filter basket pops out for lifting and swings back /latches. controls are great , easy time set . Blue lighting/ Maintains real hot coffee and shuts off after 30 mins approx. , just re push on button to re heat. Have not used timer operation but if its like the rest of the machine it will be good  Great for price and mess makers [ does not make a mess}'),
(149, 10, 1, 4, '2015-12-02', 'Four Stars Great for on the go. Its not strong enough for some frozen fruit, but will buy again'),
(150, 1, 1, 1, '2015-06-23', 'let me just tell you I LOVE KEURIG. First off, let me just tell you I LOVE KEURIG...always have and always will. I just purchased my first 2.0 brewer after owning 4 others through the years. I do love Keurig, but was not really impressed with this new 2.0. Every Kcup I brewed it had tons of coffee grounds in it....tons...was not drinkable...wasted many Kcups and a lot of creamer down the drain as I had added it to my cup before brewing. Secondly, each time I tried brewing a carafe...I was lucky to get 3/4 of a cup in the carafe. Thirdly, it took forever to brew a cup...I\'m sure I grew gray just waiting on my cup to get done brewing..it was literally a drip as it was brewing. This is the first Keurig I\'ve ever had problems with through the many years of using them. I returned my 2.0 to the store and purchased the K45 Elite in its place. I\'ve had no issues with this brewer and love it!! I could not be without a Keurig...love the convenience of one cup..which is all I drink in the mornings anyway. I love the quality of the Kcups coffee too! And best of all THANKS KEURIG, FOR THE FREE PODS FOR THIS REVIEW!!'),
(151, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-04', 'Satisfied Real nice toaster, the bread fits perfectly, toast evenly. Thank you.'),
(152, 2, 1, 3, '2015-02-20', 'Great small oven, not so great toaster I searched high and low for a basic toaster oven...It seems as though they no longer exist.  Every oven available has multiple knobs and settings; I was hoping for a model with a temperature, maybe a darkness knob for the toast knob and a sliding toaster button.  I bought this one because it was the #1 ranked toaster on Amazon.  I do not see why it received that accolade.  No matter what I do, I cannot get my toast to come out toasted but not burned. The oven aspect is fine, but the toasting option leaves a lot to be desired.'),
(153, 1, 1, 1, '2016-01-27', 'Buy a different model or brand It\'s crap. Error message daily, not what you want to deal w/ first thing in am. Buy another model or brand.'),
(154, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Five Stars good item'),
(155, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-25', 'Love it!! Love it!!  Bought this one to replace the Mini Brewer. (The Mini didn\'t have a removable reservoir, so you couldn\'t really get it clean inside.)This one has removable reservoir so you are able to clean it & it comes with a charcoal filter to remove water impurities, thereby eliminating a source of variability and poor coffee.  Has the ability to control the strength of the coffee and to make cups of 4,6,8 or 10 ounces.  Touch screen is great & easy to use!  Only problem I see, is you can\'t use 3rd-party k-cups.  But there is an insert stating they will replace the pods that don\'t work, so that\'s a plus!!Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(156, 6, 1, 3, '2015-11-22', 'Adequate but not superb This toaster is very fast, and it is easy to set the desired toast color.  A nice touch is that when the bagel switch is set, a light goes on.  But like so many other toasters, one side of the bread is well toasted and the other is not.  In fact, this is the worst toaster I have had in that regard. However it does do bagels and crumpets quite well.  You could pay a lot more and still not do any better. I remember when Cuisinart  meant upscale and expensive equipment for people who really like to cook.  Now apparently Cuisinart is a brand for those of us who have no culinary pretensions, do not want to pay too much, but want devices that do the job.'),
(157, 6, 1, 3, '2015-05-06', 'I hope this one lasts longer than my last Cuisinart toaster! I bought this toaster to replace a previous Cuisinart model of this toaster that I purchase about 5 years ago. I needed a toaster that is small because I don\'t have a lot of counter space and this one was one of the few I found that is compact. My previous Cuisinart stopped toasting on one side (the middle section stopped working; the outside sections worked okay). Like anything nowadays, repairing it wasn\'t a possibility. I hope this one lasts longer than the previous one.'),
(158, 6, 1, 5, '2016-09-15', 'Excellent Excellent toaster.  I haven\'t had any problems and have been using this toaster for months.  I\'ve never burned myself and the toast and waffles are evenly toasted.  They make a 4-slice model too that may be better for families.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(159, 10, 1, 2, '2015-05-29', 'Even if it didn\'t break, the bad design makes it worthless for larger ingredients. This thing never truly blended for me - I was just making strawberry smoothies and it would just sit there spinning away without grinding anything. It\'s a personal blender, but I feel like the design itself is off - the cup narrows dramatically just above the blades, so anything sitting on that ledge is never gonna reach. On top of that, the thing burned out after 8 months. I could probably mess around with the warranty, but I ended up buying the cheapest blender available at Costco and it is far better. Yeah, you have to clean it - but you have to clean this too, which is even more difficult because it\'s so small. Just get yourself a real blender and a cup. Forget this.'),
(160, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-10', 'Like it! I\'m getting my moneys worth!!! I got my moneys worth! I have it in white, and although it isn\'t that powerful, it works for me. I can blend greens, and frozen fruit, even apples, I\'ve had it for 2 years. The motor sometimes gets overworked, but it keeps on going, two years later. The thing of love most is that it\'s so easy to maneuver and clean, and it was so inexpensive. The think I like least is having to hold the pulse to blend, and the cup isn\'t leak proof. I use a straw if I want to take it on the go. I also would prefer a larger cup now that I am eating more fruits and veggies. They have one with a 32 ounce blender also, in Target, with this size, so two canisters, for 35 dollars, I may try that one next. It totally serves my purpose. I don\'t even really need another one, just browsing for a larger canister, maybe a bit more power, but realistically, I don\'t NEED another one, I can really pour some in another cup and make a second, with no need for a larger canister. Yes, the motor smells like it\'s burning at times, when I run it hard. It just makes me laugh, because, it is like the little engine that could. And it does, LOL. .'),
(161, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-02', 'Five Stars Excellent'),
(162, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-17', 'Perfect for testing and warming up a quick snack Replacement  for one I bought  seven years ago.  Perfect for testing and warming  up a quick  snack.'),
(163, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-20', 'Better than expected After reading through the reviews (thoroughly) I had decided to go for this coffee maker as a replacement to a DeLonghi DCF212T that I purchased from Amazon a little less than a year ago (same issues as everyone else - pot leaks, reservoir leeks, etc...).  I was pleasantly surprised by what I got (have had for 3 weeks with average of 1 to 2 pots a day). PROS:   Does not look as cheap as everyone makes out (this is a $40 dollar coffee maker  not a 3000.00 espresso machine).  I think it looks nice.   Does not leak from pot  I even overfilled and still did not get any leakage   Reservoir is well marked for multiple water/cup levels   The coffee bin CAN be removed for filling (some of the reviews do not really make clear)  has handle for easy removal for filling (I use paper filters)   Roll feet do make it very easy to pull out  I have it in the corner under a cabinet and I only need to pull out and around a few inches to get to the reservoir   Coffee temperature is just like the other coffee makers I have been through (DeLonghi, Mr Coffee, Krup) CONS:   Does stand a little taller than most makers (it is almost an inch taller than the DeLonghi) and has a small steam vent in middle of top (so condensation is collecting a little on the bottom of my cabinet)   Digital display is BRIGHT  I can handle these normally, but this one stands out (even in a kitchen 21feet x 8feet)  I resolved by simply covering it (I use the default strength/temperature and NEVER set timer so I do not really need  used chrome tape to make front look nice) As a last point, the coffee bin has a small tab on one side (to help in removal) that was snapped off.  Contacted Hamilton Beach and in a week got a replacement  no questions, no cord  just shipped out to me. So_  I took one star off for the small damage in package, but this does deserve 5 stars for being exactly what I wanted .'),
(164, 2, 1, 1, '2015-03-12', 'Item does not work. Dial will not turn down ... Item does not work. Dial will not turn down as timer ticks, ergo, it never shuts off unless you force the knob.'),
(165, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-09', 'Well Designed & Works Great Best coffeemaker I have seen. Shows evidence of well-thought designing. Doesn\'t make a mess when filling or pouring. Fairly low price is well worth it. Glad I got it.'),
(166, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-04', 'Good coffee maker Work as well as any we\'ve ever had.'),
(167, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-20', 'Five Stars Finally a product that works the way it (a toaster oven) is supposed to. Thanks Cuisinart.'),
(168, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'Black+Decker 4 slice Toaster Oven This was a gift for my daughter.  She is using it all the time and loves it.'),
(169, 7, 3, 1, '2016-01-30', 'I have purchased two of these machines in less than 2 months and today the second one quit working and will not pump the water through the system. It is a great machine if it was to work. The first machine worked for 2 weeks and did the exact same thing. I am beginning to think that it is a manufacture defect with this machine. Hamilton Beach - Please fix this problem and get a better product on the shelf for your consumers to enjoy!!!'),
(170, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-15', 'Just what I wanted. Works perfectly.  Excellent toast.'),
(171, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-05', 'Love this toaster oven... I bought this to replace the same model that I had for about 6-7 years. The coating on the element split and I decided to be better safe than sorry so replaced the entire appliance.  Looks great on the counter, toasts and broils really well, the knobs are easy to use/understand, and best of all, the crumb tray slides out from the front making it really easy to clean.  I didn\'t need anything hi-tech, and this fits the bill perfectly.'),
(172, 3, 1, 4, '2016-03-11', 'I love this thing I love this thing, but the only problem I have with it, is that there is no catch for the door. It basically drops free and it drops pretty far (almost 180 degrees if on the edge of a counter). It\'s a minor complaint, but worth mentioning'),
(173, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-06', 'THIS ONE IS A KEEPER! PERFECT!  Fits under the counter perfectly.  Does its job - good hot coffee.  Life is good with a great cup of coffee.'),
(174, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Good quality and easy to read settings Works as described. Easy to get items out after toasting is complete.'),
(175, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-16', 'Prepares my morning coffee like charm! Prepares my morning coffee like charm! Brews it nicely too and makes the blend more aromatic and savory.'),
(176, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-11', 'Use the Bunn Filters in this Maker Better when you use the Bunn filters.  If you like strong coffee and use a standard coffee scoop this maker is OK when you use the Bunn filters.  If you use cheap filters they overflow the top of the filter.  The basket is not huge on this coffee maker.  The Bunn filters are a little taller and maybe also flow a little faster so they do not overflow when using a lot of scoops of coffee.'),
(177, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-23', 'So far so good. It fits perfectly on our little counter in ... I bought this for our little store so maybe we would quit eating out so much.  So far so good.  It fits perfectly on our little counter in the kitchen area and looks good too.  So far its been cooking its heart out and no problems.  If something goes wrong I will update.'),
(178, 7, 3, 4, '2015-05-19', 'Compact and user friendly, this coffee maker is much more flexible than my Keurig 2.0. It uses K-cup pods or my favorite ground coffee. There are three cups that fit in the brew head, an over all cup that holds the brew basket and the K-cup basket. Lift out the K-cup basket to use grounds, which has a MAX mark for convenience. The water reservoir has a lift out basket with 8, 10, and 14 oz marks for water. How much you put in is how much you get out, it doesnt hold extra water. The cup rest can be moved up one notch to fit smaller cups. The power button offers \"strong\" brew and regular brew. When all is set up and the power button is pushed, it takes about 45 seconds to know it is doing anything, then is starts to make slight \'boiling\' sounds then a murring sound as the coffee starts filling the cup. The whole brewing process takes less than three minutes. My favorite part of the coffee maker is that I can use grounds, which are less expensive. Yet I still have the fancy of using a K-cup pod if I wish. I have it set up in my home office, which is uber convenient. If I had found this maker first, it is the one I would have bought over the Keurig.'),
(179, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-29', 'Four Stars good'),
(180, 3, 1, 4, '2015-03-30', 'Good but not great This toaster oven is good for reheating leftovers. It makes good toast and waffles but I will say it\'s slower than my past toaster oven. To be fair... My last toaster oven was $200 and it finally died after about 4 years of everyday use. I wasn\'t in the mood to spend $200 this day so I bought this oven and can say I am disappointed but it\'s definitely not as fast.'),
(181, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Five Stars Makes great coffee, hot and fast.  Coffee pours without dripping.'),
(182, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-24', 'My husband and I really enjoy our new Keurig K250 2 My husband and I really enjoy our new Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing System.  We have found a wide selection of coffee to choose from. Pricing is usually under 75 cents per pod.  Where can you buy a cup of great tasting coffee for under a dollar anymore?  When company is over they get excited about making a selection from the Pod Storage Tray that we purchased to sit the machine on.  I would highly recommend a Keurig 2.0 brewing system to anyone who asks.  Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(183, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-17', 'Too complicated to figure out the settings It\'s cheap but not the easiest  to figure out the settings. I have burned some toast so far. It should not be this complicated for a cheap toaster oven. The crumb tray is ok but it inserted through the oven door not under it how my other toasters had it in the past. It\'s small enough not to look too bulky on the counter but not high quality. Looks a bit cheap but for the price you get what you paid for.'),
(184, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-07', 'Works well but the writing at the dials is hard ... Works well but the writing at the dials is hard to read with my old eyes. Needs bigger and fatter print.'),
(185, 9, 1, 5, '2015-07-06', 'Five Stars great coffee maker.'),
(186, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'Five Stars Use it everyday.'),
(187, 6, 1, 3, '2017-01-10', 'I do like that it has four nice large slots Okay for toasting.  Sometimes the settings seem off - it\'ll be set on a 2 and it barely toasts, but set it on 3 and it\'s too dark.  Also the left two slots seem to toast differently than the right two slots.  I do like that it has four nice large slots.  Hamburger buns and bagels fit easily.  Gets the job done, but wish the settings were more accurate.'),
(188, 11, 1, 1, '2014-07-13', 'One Star Has about as much power as a lite bright.'),
(189, 4, 1, 2, '2015-06-14', 'I\'ll be buying the next one from Costco so if it ever breaks I can easily return it and it won\'t bee a Cuisinart It didn\'t last.  At first the top heating elements stopped working, now the unit will not turn off unless it is unplugged from the wall.  Why can\'t anyone make a toaster oven that lasts?  It is still under warranty but is too much of a hassle and too expensive to return to get repaired.  I\'ll be buying the next one from Costco so if it ever breaks I can easily return it and it won\'t bee a Cuisinart. Otherwise we really liked the unit.  Too bad nothing is made to last anymore.'),
(190, 4, 1, 1, '2016-09-17', 'I would not buy again and would not recommend. The beeping is annoying as is the need ... Mine lasted two years before the top heating element stopped working.  I would not buy again and would not recommend.  The beeping is annoying as is the need to always set a time when baking.'),
(191, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'Love it! It\'s big enough Love it!  It\'s big enough, but still fits in my small kitchen.'),
(192, 8, 1, 4, '2015-02-28', 'For the money, it\'s ok For the price, it works for me.  It does leak a little bit of water around the lid from condensation, and the lack of auto-shutoff is disappointing.  What do you expect for the money though.....'),
(193, 6, 1, 2, '2017-01-13', 'Doesn\'t work well in the long term Love the raise up feature. Toasted beautifully the first couple of months, now it doesn\'t toast evenly at all. Have turn it around and go through multiple cycles.'),
(194, 5, 1, 4, '2016-02-21', '... this for a few days now and am overall happy with it I have had this for a few days now and am overall happy with it. Pros: Very easy to use, looks nice on the counter, is by far the easiest coffee pot to clean I\'ve ever purchased, the price was great. Cons: Slow brewing (especially if you use the bold setting) and I also noticed that it doesn\'t get very hot. If you\'re not willing to spend more money (which I wasn\'t at this point), I\'m not sure you can beat this one.'),
(195, 4, 1, 2, '2015-06-09', 'Oven coil warps While I loved the toaster oven features, especially the pull out crumb tray, after about a year and a half, the heating coil began to wrap up toward the top of the oven.  This burns e everything on one side and makes it impossible to slide the rack in on the lower setting.  I also wonder about safety.  Unfortunately my Amazon return window is well past.'),
(196, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-01', 'Great for cooking nuggets and other small things for the ... Great for cooking nuggets and other small things for the kids. Takes a couple minutes to heat up VS 10-15 or so minutes for a large oven.'),
(197, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-06', 'Love LOVE my new machine Love LOVE my new machine!!!! So easy and love all the new features!!! So happy with this purchase!!!  Thank you Keurig for the free pods for this review! :) :)'),
(198, 4, 1, 3, '2016-06-11', 'Three Stars Smaller than I thought and could not make the tray extension when opening the door work!'),
(199, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-18', 'Five Stars Makes great coffee when I want it. Does what it is supposed to do.'),
(200, 4, 1, 2, '2016-08-23', 'Defective Product, Needs Recall The toaster lasted 5 years until the heating element malfunctioned, which seems to be a common defect. Mine gave a warning sign by randomly shutting off and beeping on bake. After another attempt, I watched the lower front heating element immediately split open and melted. The unit wouldn\'t shut off and the plug had to be pulled.'),
(201, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-12', 'Five Stars handy blender for one person'),
(202, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-03', 'Great toaster Great toaster, the white is easy to keep clean, size is easy to store in my cabinet.'),
(203, 5, 1, 2, '2014-12-20', 'I am just disappointed that I spent my hard earned money on this This item lasted less than 1 year.  I had hoped that it would last much longer.  It was not abused.  In fact, I only used it every other day.  I am just disappointed that I spent my hard earned money on this.  I wouldn\'t advise buying this.'),
(204, 5, 1, 1, '2015-10-27', 'Worked great!, for 6 whole months..... Purchased on May3rd, 2015.  Stopped working before Oct 23rd, 2015.  Worked great for 6 months....expected a longer life span.'),
(205, 3, 1, 3, '2016-07-21', 'Three Stars good but takes time to figure it out.'),
(206, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-28', 'Great Buy! We purchased this toaster over for our small office, and we use it ALL THE TIME!  It has many settings and cooks a variety of things.  Everyone uses it and we have no complaints.  Great product for the price!'),
(207, 10, 1, 1, '2015-07-27', 'Breaks down in 2 months. Broke down after 2 months, can\'t return or get money back. But it costs $15 so don\'t know what I was expecting. Guess I\'ll just order a new one. I think the best play is to buy a more expensive one that is reliable if you have the funds to do so.'),
(208, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-06', 'Best coffee maker I\'ve owned. Excellent coffee pot. Brews perfect coffee.'),
(209, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-22', 'Five Stars great looking plenty of room to bake buns which I have done'),
(210, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-29', 'Perfect for keeping on counter under upper cabinets! Just to clarify how this works:  There is a button on the right side that releases the front swinging door which contains the basket where you place the coffee grinds.  This basket is removable.  (It uses flat bottomed coffee filters).  The entire unit swivels in both directions in place to access the back of the unit. This is where the reservoir that you fill with water.  The reservoir completely detaches from the unit to allow you to fill it at the sink then replace. The beauty of these features (the front swinging basket door, the swiveling unit, the removable reservoir) is that you can place this coffee maker on your counter, under the upper cabinets, and not have to pull it out every time you want to fill it up or clean it.  Its ingenious.  It has a clock, a brew time programmer, 1-4 cup brew setting, regular brew setting, and bold setting, and 3 temperature setting for how hot you want the hot plate while it stays warm after brewing.  I love this coffee maker.  It has cluttered and simplified my kitchen counter space.'),
(211, 6, 1, 1, '2015-03-12', 'Worst toaster ever This is the worst toaster I have ever owned. The toasting is inconsistent at best. We have burnt more toast and bagels than we have made good toast. A three one day is good and burns the toast the next day. Even when the toast is not burnt, it is good on one side and hardly toasted on the other. The controller is very loose and gets changed by accident all of the time. We watch for that now and is not the reason that everything gets burnt. We now have it set at less than 3. I would hate to see what a 7 would be, probably charcoal. Save your money and get another brand.'),
(212, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'Five Stars It is the best toaster I\'ve ever had.  The toaster heats up very fast, toast in no time!'),
(213, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Perfect Bought this for a Christmas gift and they love it.  Definitely is exactly what they needed in a small kitchen.'),
(214, 6, 1, 1, '2016-01-24', 'One Star Defective auto off is not working!! It burned the breads and it is smoking when I use it.'),
(215, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-30', 'love it!! Love my new oven.  I have a gas stove but really like a broil feature.  Have had this for a couple of weeks and have made grilled cheese (the English way), pizza and quiche.  This is my new go to for making food.  I haven\'t had any issues with the controls as described by others.'),
(216, 8, 1, 4, '2014-01-15', 'Great buy, space saver, full pot is good for 1-2 people This coffee maker does it\'s job at a great price. I bought it for my dorm room about a year ago. It still works great. I\'m giving it 4 stars though because it doesn\'t have an automatic turn off so be wary of that and remember to turn it off.'),
(217, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-26', 'Great toaster The first one did not work properly and sent it back with no problem. The second one works great, have to get use to all the settings.'),
(218, 6, 1, 3, '2015-05-14', 'So-so Toaster This is a great toaster if you only want to toast one side of your bread.  You will not need the bagel setting because the regular setting will make the side facing the inside of the toaster nice and brown and the side facing the outside of the toaster mostly white.  But, it was very inexpensive, and it pops up nicely.  We\'ll see how long it lasts.  Even though I had my doubts about this toaster, I found the reviews on more expensive toasters to be quite problematic.  If the expensive ones weren\'t very good, why not get a cheap one?'),
(219, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-18', 'very nice! Haven\'t used yet but seems ok Yes.....very nice !  Haven\'t used yet but seems ok,.....'),
(220, 1, 1, 1, '2016-04-03', 'One Star Returned after it failed 3 times in first 10 uses.  Too much electronics that doesn\'t work properly.'),
(221, 9, 1, 4, '2015-12-14', 'Four Stars Easy to use, makes a great cup of coffee.'),
(222, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-16', 'Great oven. Works great. Makes great toast quickly. Recommend to all.'),
(223, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'Five Stars It makes an excellent cup of coffee and is easy to use.'),
(224, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'Five Stars awesome'),
(225, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-12', 'Five Stars For the price it rocks.'),
(226, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-20', 'Works like a dream! Fits the bill exactly. Here\'s why: 1. I can add water without having to take all the guts out, 2. it has a long-ish power cord so I can slide it out from under my cabinets enough to fill it with water without having to re-arrange my appliances, 3. I can see how much coffee is left in the tank (I can make more when needed at parties and not wait for someone to surprise me and say it\'s empty), 4. it has a lever on the exterior of the machine to dispense the coffee (no burned hands/wasted coffee), 5. I can place a normal coffee cup on the drip tray under the dispenser, 6. it has a water filter - and - bonus(!), 7. a light to see the coffee whilst filling the cup. I would highly recommend this. The price point is a little high, but you\'ll be glad you spent the money on this after using it once. Other than someone else making coffee for me every day, this is the next best thing.'),
(227, 5, 1, 2, '2016-05-13', 'Both leaked! great design with the removable water dispenser.  Has a bright blue light that might bother some people.  HOWEVER, the serious issue was that two coffee makers leaked a little from the bottom. I can understand one leaking but two indicates there is a serious design problem.  Amazon was GREAT but it is a hassle to box the item up and take it to UPS.'),
(228, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-28', 'Wonderful ! i love this thing. it is perfect for what i needed. sure the lid could be a little more sturdy but it does not interfere with performance.  Just buy a few lid & bucket replacements and your set for a while.'),
(229, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-01', 'Five Stars Perfect'),
(230, 10, 1, 1, '2016-01-30', 'Leaks I was so excited to use this, but when I opened it and put in some fruit, and it wouldn\'t run.  I tried to add liquid to see if it would help start things moving, but quickly realized my blender was sitting in a puddle since the liquid was dripping through.  For some reason when i took it out of the box, the blade and rubber gasket were loose and not even at a straight angle, so the blender doesn\'t work and the liquid drips out right away.  Probably just got a defected one, but I\'m disappointed.'),
(231, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-09', 'Superb Quality for a Kitchen Home Appliance Superb quality for a kitchen appliance! I purchased one to give away to my newly wed friends as a gift and they absolutely LOVED it. Be sure to check all buttons for proper usage to avoid confusion but nonetheless this product brand has been tested and proven to be excellent. I own a similar toaster and have been with me for years with no problem whatsoever. Highly recommend!'),
(232, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-20', 'Five Stars Best coffee make ever'),
(233, 6, 1, 4, '2014-11-20', 'Nice toaster. The sides stay cool to the touch Nice toaster. The sides stay cool to the touch, love the pull out crumb tray and the defrost button. Only four stars because I have to push everything down twice because even on the highest setting it doesn\'t toast very dark, otherwise I would love it!'),
(234, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-04', 'Perfect housewarming gift. My girlfriend loved it!  Given as house warming gift and uses it daily instead of heating large oven.'),
(235, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-24', 'Love this toaster! This toaster works wonders! It works better than any other one I\'ve had! And it\'s not too big, so it doesn\'t take up much room on my kitchen table.'),
(236, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Great apartment sized coffee maker Great apartment sized coffee maker. No crazy bells and whistles, just a coffee maker with a flip switch. Uses the small size filter and makes about 5 cups (or two big mugs) of coffee.'),
(237, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Keurig makes my morning routines go by alot faster, ... Keurig makes my morning routines go by alot faster, theres barely any cleanup & brewing time is so much fasted! Dont know why I didn\'t think to buy this sooner! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review!\"'),
(238, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-06', 'Great purchase! Coffee is fantastic!!! No Complaints. I have been using it everyday for a few months. Love the programmable feature!'),
(239, 9, 1, 3, '2017-01-22', 'Great but after a month leaking. LOVE this actually. Coffee years great ( I\'m lucky). Brews a ton of coffee, way more than your standard pot. After one month the dispenser lever stopped working properly now the is a constant slow leak/drip from where you dispense. Not sure what we are going to do but for now w just put a cup under it to catch the drip.'),
(240, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-14', 'Five Stars Have not used yet, but I\'m sure it will work well!.'),
(241, 10, 1, 4, '2015-12-18', 'Nice little blender Nice little blender. I mainly use it for mixing simple stuff like protein shakes and other blends. It\'s also not a loud blender compared to other I had in the past.'),
(242, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-16', 'I\'m 100% satisfied! I have been married for over 36 years and have gone through many coffee makers and this one takes the cake!  I\'m 100% satisfied!'),
(243, 12, 1, 4, '2016-06-29', 'Cool looking design Cool looking design, works good, but no release for crumbs. Still not sure how to solve that besides holding upside while shaking.'),
(244, 9, 1, 1, '2015-05-15', 'Seems like the consumer always loses out Coffee maker costs more than it can deliver .  Seems like the consumer always loses out. Plastic and hard to clean.  First cup is hot but the additional cups are luke warm. Hard to return to Cuisinart.'),
(245, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Five Stars Works great1'),
(246, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-21', 'Five Stars GREAT! As advertised!'),
(247, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-03', 'Five Stars Very nice.'),
(248, 5, 1, 2, '2014-08-17', 'Broke after 4 months of occasional use This WAS a great coffee maker, and I loved the coffee that it made as well as the ability to programmable feature. However, after 4 months of occasional use (I also have a Keurig and use that on most mornings), the coffee maker just completely quit working. I noticed that the clock light was off, and when I tried to unplug it and restart it, nothing happened. It\'s totally useless now. I spent a lot of money on a coffee maker that I\'ve used only about 25 times, so I would NOT recommend this product.'),
(249, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-09', 'Five Stars it works fine but is a little small for 4 slices imho.'),
(250, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-12', 'Five Stars works great. Coffe is great. Nice design'),
(251, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-31', 'Five Stars good job service was great we used it a lot better then  a micro wave  thank you'),
(252, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Five Stars great buy makes life so much easier'),
(253, 7, 3, 4, '2016-10-05', 'it works pretty well, i do not use the pre-prepared cups but use my own coffee.'),
(254, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-12', 'Five Stars love the cancel button now the toast doesn\'t fly through the air when you cut the toast cycle short.'),
(255, 12, 1, 4, '2016-08-23', 'Bracket Feature is the BEST! My mom loves this toaster oven.  It is the only one that has the brackets to slide out the rack when you open the oven door.  Prevents getting your  fingers burned reaching in for the rack (even if you have a pot holder).  She loves that feature and for some reason no other toaster oven has it including the larger more expensive Hamilton Beach I initially got for her.  I sent it back and got this one and she is so happy.  It is too small in my opinion but she loves it.'),
(256, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-19', 'One Star Broke within a month'),
(257, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-07', 'My parents love it. Got this for my parents and they love it.  Their kids have all left the nest, so this keeps them from needing to use the oven most days, and gives them a second oven to use for big family dinners. They are pretty critical people and I haven\'t heard a word of complaint, much to my own surprise.'),
(258, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-03', 'Great for clay Have been using this for,polymer clay and it works great. I was surprised how quick is came and how affordable it was. $20 for a black and decker you can\'t go wrong!'),
(259, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Five Stars Good Toaster !'),
(260, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-19', 'Great coffee machine for more than 4 cups daily I have been using this Cuisnart Model for a log time and I havd been very pleased with the quality of coffee it makes. It is very solid, nice design, easy to use, and brew excellent coffee. It has lots of nice convenient features such as Alarm notifying you when coffee is ready. My only issue is that there is too much work to do cleaning afterward for just makig a two cup of coffee per day, otherwise, I would still like to us it. I have only replaced it once in the past 7 yers and that was because, I just wanted a new one. I should point out that the French Company cuisnart in USA have great custome service and provide a two year warranty with free shipping in California for any of their products. On My case they replaced it for Free knowing that I had mine for over 6 years and I just paid shipping. unfortunatley all the reviews give me pause to think before spending more money. I had recently purchased a brand name but, unfortunatley had to return it b/c it was making a mess and too much drips , etc. So still looking around for a small two to three cups quality coffee maker...!'),
(261, 7, 3, 2, '2017-01-04', 'I don\'t know if its just mine but ever since I bought it, whenever the water is brewing out it makes a loud obnoxious noise. Not a noise you can just ignore. My bad for throwing the box out right away because I am stuck with it and looking for another one. Waste of money.'),
(262, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-06', 'Simple and inexpensive Mostly gets used for toast which it does very evenly. We\'ve made a small pizza in it and it worked great. Cannot be beat for the price.  I really like the absence of a clock and other digital controls.'),
(263, 2, 1, 2, '2016-09-04', 'Power cord too short It looks very nice and matches my kitchen appliances. I have used it only a few times and it was good so far. But the power cord is ridiculously short and every time I want to use my toaster I have to move it from the corner shown in the picture closer to the outlet socket. I double checked and cord length is not mentioned in product description. Such a shame!.'),
(264, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-16', 'Love Coffee and Love my Keurig K250 I Love the Keurig K250 its small compact Makes one cup of coffee or a carafe sits nice on my counter and is super easy to use! I love that it also has a touch screen display and it makes a super fast cup of coffee. I would totally recommend this Keurig K250 2.0 my family loves drinking coffee and we love Keurig and I received the product free for testing!'),
(265, 3, 1, 5, '2015-10-02', 'Excellent oven Great purchase. Oven meets all my expectations. Very convenient and efficient.  I have used it several times for different food items from baking a cake to reheating pizza. Controls easy to use.  Would definitely recommend to others.'),
(266, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-05', 'I got one of these used at a yard sale ... I got one of these used at a yard sale two years ago and it\'s served me well thus far. The size is barely larger than an average toaster, so it\'s ideal for a small kitchen. There is an issue with the oven portion, in that if you\'re using it to make something that takes a while you need to toss a kitchen towel or a hot mitt on top of the toaster because the closure for the top is rather thin.'),
(267, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-13', 'Good product for a good price. I needed a coffee maker specifically to make my iced coffee for a few days and store in the fridge. I didn\'t want a single serve, but I also didn\'t need 8 cups. This was the perfect size, it doesn\'t leak like some other coffee makers and the price is great. If you\'re looking for a simple machine to make coffee this is it.'),
(268, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-15', 'Works great. My only complaint is the lowest temp is ... Works great.My only complaint is the lowest temp is 200 degrees F. I like to cook some items at 175 degrees F but am unable to do so with this oven. Otherwise, it is great.'),
(269, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-06', 'Defective product, should be recalled I bought this oven in the middle of 2011. I was very happy with the purchase at first. It is roomy, you can use it for baking small dishes, toasting, etc. The oven was working ok until a few months ago, when the heating bar started to bend upwards. Then it started cracking burning the toast in the proximity of the crack. Within the last few weeks the cracks started to multiply like crazy and a see a new one starting on the other heating bar. I\'m retiring it as of today. I think for the prize the oven should last longer than 4 years. I had a Black&Decker oven that I bought for $20 and it lasted 10 years. This product is a major fire hazard.'),
(270, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-30', 'Wonderful Product, Great Seller This is my 2nd Cuisinart toaster and obviously, I love it.'),
(271, 12, 1, 4, '2016-11-28', 'Pretty practical and versatile Pretty practical and versatile.  Only downside is it doesn\'t toast very evenly across the bread, and seems to take longer than a normal toaster, but it\'s only a small difference.'),
(272, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-26', 'Wasted my money When I used this blender for the first time I  started smelling smoke and it cut off and never came back on. I would\'ve returned it but because of issues I\'ve read from people trying to return items I didn\'t want to go thru that, besides I had already thrown the box it came in away'),
(273, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'My Keurtig order! Keurig arrived in open Keurig box.  Very disappointed not in plain cardboard box.  Top of box was open.  Anyone going past our house could see it!  Blessed no one picked it up.  Never has of my orders arrived this way.  Just hoping my new Keurig works.'),
(274, 6, 1, 3, '2014-05-08', 'Not what I was hoping for When I got it out I put toast in on the wrong side-not the one-slice section.  It burned the toast pretty badly, in fact the toast was smoking.  It\'s pretty hit or miss on toasting.'),
(275, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-24', 'A GOOD TOASTER OVEN A GOOD TOASTER OVEN.  COULD POSSIBLY BE IMPROVED BY USING TWO HEATING ELEMENTS TOP AND BOTTOM INSTEAD OF ONLY ONE TOP AND ONE BOTTOM.'),
(276, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-22', 'Makes great coffee and keeps it hotter for longer without developing ... Makes great coffee and keeps it hotter for longer without developing the burned flavor. Easy to clean and to use.'),
(277, 8, 1, 4, '2014-11-12', 'No frills coffee maker My expensive Keurig broke down after only a little over a year.  While I enjoyed the convenience of the Keurig, it\'s an expensive way to drink coffee (I can make a potful for what two of the pods cost), and wasteful (a trashcan full of used pods at the end of the week.)  This makes a good cup of coffee in not much more time than the Keurig and costs a fraction.  I have a big coffee maker that I can bring out for a crowd, but this one will take care of me for everyday.'),
(278, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-14', 'Super! It\'s so so so very good. It\'s just great and we love it so much. The removable water tank is awesome, the settings are easy, the machine is large enough for us, the wheeled mechanism to access the back is great. It\'s just fantastic.'),
(279, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-23', 'Awesome! Best coffee pot I have had in decades Awesome!  Best coffee pot I have had in decades!  Especially like the digital readout, you can actually see it!'),
(280, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-13', 'Love that the top cover has a spout you can ... Purchased to keep at work to make health shakes for breakfast and lunch.  Love that the top cover has a spout you can place a straw in to reduce the number of dishes to wash.  Drink straight out the blender. Works great and so many more have now purchased the same item.'),
(281, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'It\'s like the up to date version to the Elite We had the Elite version. This one is digital and came with a Carafe and bigger pods for the Carafe. It\'s like the up to date version to the Elite. Love my Kuerig.'),
(282, 11, 1, 4, '2015-08-10', 'I also like to warm up my bread (thick slices mostly) Exellent for warming pizza left overs or small pizzas. I also like to warm up my bread (thick slices mostly).'),
(283, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'Five Stars A great little toaster oven at a reasonable price!'),
(284, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'Five Stars Great'),
(285, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Love it! I am so in love with my new Keurig! I have always loved using a Keurig for the convenience of brewing one cup at a time and for being able to choose from a variety of flavors. The new Keurig 2.0 is better than ever. I like the touch screen controls as well as the variety of brewing options. It is also wonderful to have the coffee maker tell me when to refill the water, clean the unit, or perform any kind of maintenance.I never owned my own Keurig until I received the Keurig 2.0 free from Influenster for testing purposes. I feel so fortunate to be able to take part!'),
(286, 3, 1, 5, '2014-11-22', 'Quick, hot, and stylish I bought this after using an older model at my brother\'s house. PROS: Heats up super fast! Seems like less than five minutes to get to 425. Stylish - stainless steel with the digital display looks nice on your counter. It has many different functions but I only use the bake function. I\'m sure you\'d have to read the booklet to figure out what they all do. Great for reheating food quickly. CONS: The blue backlight is not sufficient to light the digital screen if your kitchen is dark. I would buy this again.'),
(287, 3, 1, 2, '2015-11-27', 'Convection quit working after a month It has some good features and seems to work fairly well. However, after only a month-and-a-half, the convection feature no longer works. After starting a bake cycle you\'re supposed to simply hit the \"Convection\" button to start the convection fan, but it refuses to come on now. We successfully used the convection feature maybe three or four times but now it\'s dead. Boxes were trashed weeks ago and 30 days have come and gone. Oh, well...'),
(288, 6, 1, 4, '2015-01-31', 'I like the way it looks and the price I spent time reading reviews about different toasters until I came across one that said, \"Why am I reading reviews.....it\'s a toaster?\"  So I stopped and picked this one.  I like the way it looks and the price.  It is working fine for what I am using it for.  I mostly toast small bagels in it.  It took a couple tries until I found that setting 2 is just about right.  I sometimes drop it back in but I learned to watch it when doing that as I threw charcoal away a couple times.  I get the impression if you were making a lot of toast that the more you do, the darker they will get or they will burn.  All in all I am happy with my choice.'),
(289, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-12', 'Five Stars Excellent'),
(290, 5, 1, 4, '2015-10-20', 'Four Stars Love this coffee maker. Works great. You cant beat the price on Amazon.'),
(291, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-12', 'Five Stars Best, easiest coffee maker and at a great price.'),
(292, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-19', 'Five Stars perfect size and great heat!'),
(293, 2, 1, 2, '2015-11-19', 'The instructions say to turn the timer knob past 10 then back to where I\'d like it which I find weird Does not toast both sides of the bread. One side comes out crispy and the other is soft. The instructions say to turn the timer knob past 10 then back to where I\'d like it which I find weird. Would not purchase again.'),
(294, 7, 3, 5, '2016-05-03', 'This works just the way I wanted it to. I can brew one cup of coffee for myself at work, either using regular coffee grounds or K-cups. Works well, easy to use, and less expensive than many other brands. So glad I purchased this so I don\'t have to drink the gross coffee my work offers!'),
(295, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-27', 'Five Stars we love it!!!'),
(296, 6, 1, 3, '2015-07-19', 'It\'s Okay. On the plus side, the sides don\'t get hot so you probably won\'t burn your hand and it doesn\'t take too much room on the counter. On the down side, the push down action on the lever isn\'t smooth and I have to toast on the # 2 setting or it burns everything.  There\'s a place on the top where crumbs fall down into so it\'s hard to clean. The bottom of my toast gets much browner than the top. The bagel setting doesn\'t seem to change how it toasts.'),
(297, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-07', 'Good buy So mini and portable! Same as pictured'),
(298, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-21', 'Great Toaster! I love this, and it saves me so much money to not use my big oven for small recipes. Not sure why people are complaining on how hard it\'s to use...like DUH, there\'s a manual, and it\'s pretty straightforward on how you can toast, bake, etc. I have no idea on how other people have written that the glass bust or the handle broke because I\'ve been using this for the past 2-3 weeks, and it\'s shows no inkling that its made poorly. Anyways, the stainless steel + black looks sleek and nice on my kitchen counter.'),
(299, 9, 1, 4, '2016-03-15', 'Love this pot I bought this Cuisinart Coffee on Demand pot to replace our 12 year old Cuisinart on demand pot that finally bit the dust.  It works fine......except for the gauge.  I had read before purchase that the gauge didn\'t work all the time....and sure enough it doesn\'t.  I just slap it on the side and that usually gets it to working. I gave it only 4 stars because of the faulty gauge.'),
(300, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-19', 'good price! easy to use and doesn\'t take up ... good price!  easy to use and doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space.'),
(301, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-15', 'Five Stars Excellent coffee every morning, who needs Starbucks'),
(302, 2, 1, 3, '2016-06-27', 'OK but not Great! I have had Black +Decker toaster ovens for year.  This newer model seems smaller because some things no longer fit because the height is less than older models.  For example, trying to reheat popovers is impossible because they are too high to fit.  Also, older models were designed so that the oven rack rolled out when the door opened.  The new model does not have this feature so you have to use a pot holder each time you pull the rack out.'),
(303, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-07', 'Five Stars Toaster oven works great.'),
(304, 4, 1, 5, '2016-07-06', 'Five Stars Auto shut off great feature'),
(305, 5, 1, 1, '2014-02-09', 'NOT very hot! If the coffee actually came out hot it would be fine.  More like luke warm.  Terrible. Would not buy or recommend.  Wish i had kept the box for a return.'),
(306, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-31', 'I\'m in love! It does everything I could imagine that I want.  Am very happy with this purchase.'),
(307, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-17', 'LOVE it - How did I ever do without this. LOVE it - easy to set up and use. Burned the first set of waffles, but then got the hang of it...Made excellent frozen pizza and garlic bread, crisped breakfast pastries and bake at home sourdough bread to a just like from the bakery taste.  How did I ever do without this?  Just wish it came with an easy to read manual and maybe a cookbook..'),
(308, 9, 1, 4, '2015-11-23', 'I like it. I recommend it to anyone Plain and simple, I like it. I recommend it to anyone.'),
(309, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-20', 'Love it We purchased this after using our daughter\'s Cuisinart. Makes great coffee, and grabbing a cup is easy!'),
(310, 12, 1, 5, '2015-12-29', 'Very Pleased This does a great job and doesn\'t take up much space on my countertop. In a kitchen that is micro chromatic it adds a nice splash of color. It toasts nicely. I had a very expensive Cuisinart toaster that did not do as well.'),
(311, 10, 1, 1, '2015-06-03', 'Burned the first time plugging it! it burned the first time I plugged it in. I had a refund anyway...'),
(312, 2, 1, 3, '2016-09-01', 'Toaster is great for the price Toaster is great for the price , Problem is the Contrast of the lettering around the knobs and they wear off too easily , But it does Toast well.'),
(313, 6, 1, 1, '2014-02-15', 'Never buy Cuisinart product again. Have tried everything and this toaster will not toast one slice of bread in any slot. Wigfe hates it and she wants old one back.'),
(314, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-12', 'Great quality at a great price Great quality at a great price. I got this for my wife and she loves it. Better that other more expensive machines'),
(315, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-20', 'a perfect morning must have!!! I love love love this machine!!!...'),
(316, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-26', 'I needed a small, individual, coffee maker for upcoming guest. This model was dependable, made a great cup of coffee, and versatile. I have nothing but good things to say about this model. Thumbs Up!'),
(317, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-01', 'unbelievably amazing I still can\'t believe how affordable this amazing coffeemaker is! It makes wonderful coffee, it\'s very easy to use, and the water carafe is removable and can be filled in the sink. It\'s soooo affordable!'),
(318, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-27', 'Great Oven Works great. I purchased to to go with our new motor home. Our new motor home does not have an oven, and I just can\'t live without one. Bakes bread and potato\'s perfect.'),
(319, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-25', 'Five Stars awesome'),
(320, 2, 1, 1, '2016-01-31', 'The controls are very imprecise, so it\'s very difficult ... The controls are very imprecise, so it\'s very difficult to control how dark (or light) you want to toast your bread.  It\'s just a dial, so you every time you toast something, you\'re guessing on how dark it will get because the icons that show the levels of toast darkness aren\'t even that accurate.  If you need to take out the toast before the time is up, it does not automatically turn off, so you end up wasting energy just letting it run its course without anything in there.  I have always found Black & Decker products to be really straight-forward and solid, but this one really disappoints.  I just returned it and am buying a Breville.'),
(321, 6, 1, 5, '2014-02-06', 'Toaster I had a more expensive toaster before.  I hated it.  This one is so much better and I like the white.'),
(322, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', '... and hot and warms my meat just as I like it. It\'s big and hot and warms my meat just as I like it.'),
(323, 4, 1, 2, '2015-05-06', 'Made with cheap materials that fail too early Like the other reviewers, I purchased because of its size, stylish looks and lack of annoying clicking timer for toast (the electronic multi-beep is also annoying, but less so). I bought this at Bed, Bath & Beyond with 20% coupon. It never produced evenly toasted bread, but that wasnt the deal killer. While my previous GE Toast-R-Oven lasted 8-10 years, this failed after 4 years of very light duty. Daily toast and occasional oven usage. Now the thermostat doesnt work properly clicking on & off repeatedly trying to find a cycle and the covering over the heating coil has split open. Just cheap materials and poor engineering for a $70 appliance. Better to find a $20 Black & Decker and toss it after a couple of years. Would not experiment with a higher model Cuisinart unless I found it at a garage sale.'),
(324, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-21', 'Does a good job! Great toaster, toasts the whole slice.  Easily adjusted for shade and  doneness.'),
(325, 6, 1, 4, '2014-11-11', 'Four Stars good value.'),
(326, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-07', 'Save your money and get a better blender, because you will just end up replacing ... Could barely chop up ice. Save your money and get a better blender, because you will just end up replacing this one within a week or two.'),
(327, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-13', 'One of the best drip coffee systems we\'ve ever used One of the best drip coffee systems we\'ve ever used.  I love the \"coffee gauge\" and the fact that you can pour while its brewing w/out any issues.  Great design.'),
(328, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'Top-notch, inexpensive, toaster oven This is an excellent and quite inexpensive toaster oven for general-purpose toasting and baking, etc.  it heats very quickly, and its toasting ability is excellent.  This unit actually replaced a Cuisinart T0B-40 oven -- which cost more than twice as much -- yet I think this oven is superior in nearly every respect except total inside capacity.  This unit also came with a heavy-duty 3-wire grounded power cord, something the more-expensive Cuisinart did not have! This unit is in my view very highly recommended!'),
(329, 6, 1, 1, '2014-01-13', 'Burned - unpredictable Sometimes it toasted up without any color...once our entire home filled with thick black smoke it was burned so much.  Uneven toasting....simply unusable and we had to purchase a different toaster...  Please don\'t buy this toaster!!!'),
(330, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-07', 'I do like \"cancel\" button that sill pop the bread up early In both slots, one side of the bread browns faster than the other. Not a huge problem, but I had to get used to it. I do like \"cancel\" button that sill pop the bread up early, rather than forcing it by means of the lever.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(331, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'The Keurig K250 - Small on Size Big on Features and Functionality If you are looking for the perfect brewer for your desk at work, this is it. The Keurig 2.0 system has some great features - such as increased brew strength (great for those tough Monday mornings, hot water on demand (Earl Grey here we come), and an easy to use touch screen interface. The 40 oz. reservoir ensures that you will not be making constant trips to the water cooler for refills. I recently was able to make use of the cleaning feature which is an added bonus to make sure the insert tip is clean and functional. This was very easy to use and made routine maintenance a breeze. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(332, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-31', 'Good coffee maker very easy to use and works great.'),
(333, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-23', 'Good, basic toaster oven. Don\'t waste your money on a more expensive model After more than one expensive toaster oven going belly up within 3-4 years, we decided to just stick to inexpensive toaster ovens. This is our second Black and Decker toaster oven in about 6 years. The previous one is very similar to this model. Actually the one this one replaced still worked, just not very well (it didn\'t toast evenly, as one heat element had given out). So far, so good. We bought this one based upon the decent reviews here on Amazon and the low price. We use it 2-3 times a day, almost every day of the week. Mostly to toast bread, but also occasionally to cook or re-heat food since we don\'t like and don\'t own a microwave.'),
(334, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-25', 'BUYER BEWARE CHEAPLY MADE I was given two of these toasters for Christmas this morning and they BOTH were broken. They each had one cheap plastic leg broken off in the packaging.. Can\'t even use it this morning. Save yourself the pain and spend the extra money on a higher quality product.'),
(335, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'I love my Keurig K250 I love my Keurig K250!!! As a law student, you can never have to much coffee, and more important is your time. I use this for pretty much all my needs. I have K-cups for iced tea, coffee, hot chocolate, tea, etc. When i want a nice chill night to study, i love brewing a cup of tea! Its small, cute, and very convienent. I love the color of my truquoise one! It goes great with the theme of my kitchen decor. I think it\'s sort of touchscreen! And it came with everything; Carafe, cleaning solution, filters, free K-cups, etc. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(336, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-30', 'love it. True to description; quick delivery; love it.'),
(337, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-06', 'Perfect for Single Serve This is great for what I use it for, single serve shakes. What you see in the picture is 12oz. I just mix up my protein powder in milk but I\'ve never put ice in it or something like fruit. It only has one button which works for me and I love that it turns right into a travel mug. I take it to go and one less thing to wash, brilliant idea.'),
(338, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'great This works so well...easy to clean...my husband was able to make himself a snack with a ton of mess...YEA!!!'),
(339, 5, 1, 1, '2016-09-06', 'Dont buy It quit working after just 4 months!  I\'m not able to return this.  I feel cheated.'),
(340, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'I love my Keurig I love my Keurig, its quick and easy and a great way to start the morning.  This sized Keurig is very flexible, it is good for single use or if you want to make a pot of coffee for a group.  The Keurig is actually what got me into loving coffee, it brightens my morning a lot more now.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(341, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-25', 'Five Stars Fantastic quality for the price and it looks sleek too :)'),
(342, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-06', 'Works pretty well. Works pretty well.  This heats things reasonably quickly.  I choose to be healthier and NOT use a microwave, so I use this as well as an Induction Cooktop and a Pressure Cooker to cook nearly everything I do... This warms up tortillas and little things like that.  The Induction Cooktop takes care of all my \"real metal\" (non-aluminum, non-conductive) pots & pans.  I prefer to use stainless steel or cast iron cookware so the PIC works great.'),
(343, 10, 1, 3, '2015-10-31', 'lacks power This works best on softer things you\'re wanting to mix, but not particularly powerful for anything frozen or too chunky.  It just feels cheap, but I love the idea of mixing it and taking it to go.'),
(344, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-04', 'Well made, looks good Like the brewing bold option even if it takes a while.  Doesn\'t take up too much counter space and basket and carafe are easy to clean.'),
(345, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'Five Stars Perfect for breakfast bagles'),
(346, 6, 1, 1, '2016-09-25', 'One Star Toasts only on one side.  I must flip my bread around and toast twice to get toast.'),
(347, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Love the choice of cup Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I would have written one any way. Love the choice of cup, mug, or carafe. Choice of color on light is very nice.'),
(348, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-24', 'Less than 2 months old and the motor already went ... Less than 2 months old and the motor already went out.  Bought 1/5/15, today is 2/24/15 and its broken.  Used it for protein shakes'),
(349, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-26', 'Terrific Best coffee ever.  Nice looking. And inexpensive.  Size is good and easy to clean up after use. Now I just wish the coffee beans were cheaper!'),
(350, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-12', 'Five Stars I highly recommend this coffeemaker for our office. In fact I may buy one for my home use.'),
(351, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Five Stars This is a good product, I needed a small blender and it seems to do the job.'),
(352, 8, 1, 5, '2015-10-31', 'Great Little Coffeemaker Great little coffee maker.  Replaced a similar one I had that after 5 years gave up the ghost.  Makes a nice hot cup of coffee and doesn\'t take long to brew.'),
(353, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-10', 'NO TIMER FOR BAKING. No timer for baking and that was a deal breaker for me. I returned it. I purchased it at B, B and Beyond. Who wants a toaster oven with no ability to turn itself off? I don\'t. The sales people were shocked when I told them I was returning it for not having a timer. They had never seen a toaster oven with no timer or one that doesn\'t turn itself off. It will keep on heating up and burn everything if you don\'t watch it. Heated up much too quickly and burnt my knish in 15 minutes on 325. You have to watch what you are baking very carefully, and for small items that\'s a hassle. It will shut off for toast, but unlike other toaster ovens, no timer for baking or shut off. It\'s cheap and cheesy in feel. It looks cheap. The baking tray is a cheap and thin. Not up to Cuisinart standards, but these days, none of their products are what they used to be.'),
(354, 7, 3, 1, '2015-12-14', 'Very disappointed. Tried brewing a cup of coffee. It made coffee but was not hot. Tried a second time same thing. For a third time with plan water and it finally heated the liquid. So I tried again with coffee and once again came out cold. I will be returning it today. I really was excited about the price. I guess you get what you pay for. :('),
(355, 5, 1, 3, '2016-01-07', 'I have really enjoyed this coffee maker I have really enjoyed this coffee maker. Love the options, but the size option wont work as designed. I have fill the water reservoir to the top line and set the brew to the 1-4 setting.... and then came back to a tea colored full pot of coffee... at 5am this is not what you want to see.'),
(356, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'Five Stars perfect item. works very well'),
(357, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-17', 'Five Stars This keeps the coffee hot without scorching it.'),
(358, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-09', 'Great coffee maker Great coffee maker. I just fill it with the sink hose attachment, which also makes it great for iced tea because you are not putting back traces of coffee into the tank. I love the temp setting and auto turnoff.'),
(359, 1, 1, 1, '2016-06-11', 'Worst purchase, and the only thing I\'ve ever purchased three of. I just purchased my third one of these in a week. Each one lasted a few cups with the last one lasting one cup, and then it spits the last portion of each cup full of coffee grounds. This is the first product I have ever taken time to review poorly because it is soooooo bad. I really do not have the luxury of time to go buy an item three times, haul it into work and then have it , I\'m at a loss for words I\'m so mad. This would be insignificant if I didn\'t like my first cup or two to start the day so much. If I held their stock I would sell now. This will destroy their brand. Steve Smith'),
(360, 10, 1, 2, '2015-11-23', 'this sucks. This unit works ok I cannot put more than a 2 star, the motor  is very weak don\'t know how long it will last. I\'m using it and I\'m expecting the motor to go at anytime. Can\'t send it back ,lives in the Caribbean, this sucks.'),
(361, 3, 1, 5, '2014-11-24', 'Best countertop oven ever! Functions like a regular oven. Easy to use & looks great on the kitchen counter. We have two of this same model as we have a summer home. Hope they keep this one around!'),
(362, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-22', 'I like this one very much I go through coffee makers very frequently so I have tried a few.  I like this one very much.  Works as described, doesn\'t take up too much space and the removable water storage is very handy.'),
(363, 7, 3, 3, '2014-01-08', 'awkward system to manually change when you go from k-cup to regular brew. the 10oz maximum water reservoir must have been lost in the details for me... you have to fill it every use. BUT: it makes a good cup of coffee in a short amount of time and is easy to clean up. Perfect for someone who lives alone and only drinks one or 2 cups a day.'),
(364, 5, 1, 3, '2014-06-29', 'It\'s ok Makes good coffee but it is very slow.  I have been using it every day for 9 months and have yet to pour a cup of coffee without spilling some out of the pot.'),
(365, 12, 1, 4, '2016-07-31', 'Four Stars Love the oven . I use this instead of using the stove oven for small dishes.'),
(366, 9, 1, 2, '2015-09-07', 'Overpriced vis-a-vis it\'s inferior quality... IE no longetivity I have experience with tow of these.  First one bought I like very well.  At 2 year mark automated functions quit working.At year 4 all functions ceased IE dead, did not brew anything.  Sucker that I am. . replaced with another one.  Same story... programmable functions died after 2 years and ceased to brew on its 4 year anniversary IE it doesn\'t work at all.  For a hefty price of $90 one would think more quality would be built in... not so.  Better off buying a cheaper model knowing longevity is it\'s failing.'),
(367, 11, 1, 1, '2015-05-17', 'No Good Have had trouble with the door and no it is no longer usable.  I have tried to be careful with it but did not work out.  Certainly would not recommend it to anyone.'),
(368, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Awesome machine, the touch screen is great and it ... Awesome machine, the touch screen is great and it pretty much walks you thru making a cup of coffee, even tells you to add water when its time. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(369, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-20', 'I can\'t live without this thing, I use it ... I can\'t live without this thing, I use it for everything from tortilla pizzas, baked salmon & wraps & bread. The price is unbeatable, it has toast/bake& broil functions and even comes with a mini tray'),
(370, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-25', 'Four Stars It works good...I find the toasting to be a bit inconsistent.'),
(371, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-14', 'Good product I have used this coffee maker for about a month now after my Cuisinart died after a long productive life.  Found this coffee maker more convenient than my Cuisinart, has a removable water reservoir, and easy controls. Coffee taste is equal to my former coffee maker--- at half the price.  Cuisinart may be better looking although I found the Hamilton Beach reasonably attractive.'),
(372, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-24', 'Best coffee machine! Great machine. Makes good coffee, looks good and has the best ergonomics of any machine I\'ve used. Filling/emptying is really easy, and the interface is clean and easy to use.'),
(373, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-04', 'I have owned this product for appx 2 months and it is terrible. It leaks, it chooses what amount of coffee it will make, its very noisy and very slow.'),
(374, 5, 1, 3, '2015-10-15', 'Loved the design of this coffee maker but when our ... Loved the design of this coffee maker but when our power went out due a thunderstorm the coffee pot never turned back on.  Seems like a power surge damages this coffee pot.  I called Hamilton Beach and they replaced it and then it happened again and they blamed us for the power going out.  They did not replace the coffee pot a second time.  All of our outlets in the kitchen are GFI protected and no other appliances have ever not worked after a power outage.  Never had issues like this with any other coffee pots I have purchased, this one is the only one that has failed.  the coffee pot performed well while it was working and liked the removable water tank on the back and the swing basket design.  Just keep in mind when purchasing it may not work after your power goes out. It does come with a 2 yr warranty.'),
(375, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Nice product! it\'s a nice blender with an instant travel tumbler. A must-have for backpackers...'),
(376, 12, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'great space saver! I bought this for a vacation property which has a small kitchen.  I dont have a lot of room for many appliances, so buying a 2 for 1 was a smart idea.  The oven cavity is small, so you couldn\'t cook big things in there, but it\'s perfect for snacks and meals for one or two people.'),
(377, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'its a great toaster. one side more done other side less had a hard time finding 4 wide slice. you can put anything in here. even a sliced bagel. its a great toaster. one side more done other side less. would buy this again for sure. easy to clean.'),
(378, 6, 1, 4, '2016-01-15', 'Good toaster, good price. This has worked great for us, better than a pricier toaster.'),
(379, 11, 1, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Five Stars works well'),
(380, 5, 1, 3, '2015-01-08', 'This would be a great cup of coffee if it were hot This would be a great cup of coffee if it were hot.  It comes out lukewarm, and I have to put it in the microwave for 30 seconds for it to be hot.  Otherwise, I love the removable water container, and the release of the coffee filter container.'),
(381, 7, 3, 5, '2016-04-09', 'I gave it to a coworker as a gift. She loves it and says it works great.'),
(382, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-18', 'Best ever I have trie4d Mr. Coffee, Black & Decker and ever Cuisinart. None of them a re equal to the Hamilton Beach. The quality is outstanding and the price is acceptable.'),
(383, 8, 1, 4, '2015-08-14', 'I dont feel like it is actually 5 cups of coffee So I ordered this coffee pot because Im the only one that drinks coffee in my house. I figured 5 cups is way more than enough for just me. I dont feel like it is actually 5 cups of coffee, but it does fill up my travel mug with enough left for maybe 1 regular size mug. I do wish it was slightly larger. But other than that, its a coffee pot. It makes coffee, nothing fancy, no timers or anything like that, just coffee.  Which, lets be honest, isnt that what counts?'),
(384, 8, 1, 1, '2016-09-15', 'Blood instead of coffee There was a defect in the glass and it broke when I used first time. I was just trying to drink a cup of coffee but I got hurt badly..'),
(385, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-10', 'Basic Functionality - Good coffee Not bells or whistles, but it makes a decent cup of coffee. Doesn\'t have any design hiccups. If you are looking for a a basic coffee maker this is a solid choice.'),
(386, 4, 1, 1, '2015-05-25', 'Looks good but won\'t last I have now had my toaster oven for 15 months.  All was well and just what I needed for about a year.  Then the door started jamming.  I could get it opened but had to jerk it.  Now I can\'t get the door opened but just a crack.  Of course the warranty is expired.  I live alone, so it really doesn\'t get much wear and tear.  Deciding that Cuisinart should hold up better, I called them to find out  that this toaster oven had a 3 year warranty.  They are sending me a new one for $10 shipping and all i have to do is return the cord.  I like the toaster oven, so I hope this one lasts for years.'),
(387, 6, 1, 1, '2016-04-27', 'Unreliable Crap This worked okay for about the first year.  It required a lot of trial and error to figure out the right combination of settings.  For example, I found that using the \"Frozen\" button and #3 heat setting for everything seemed to yield the best results, so long as what you were toasting was room temperature.  It\'s not a perfect toaster and was sometimes frustrating, but I could live with it.  However after about a year things went downhill fast.  The toaster became stuck on the \"Bagel\" setting (even though button wasn\'t used) so everything came out more well done on one side.  Nothing could get rid of the stuck setting.  Then on low heat it started burning things.  Turned it down to #1 heat.  Still burned.  As I sit here writing this my home still reeks of burnt smoke from the last toast I attempted to make this morning.  That was the last straw, this toaster is now in the trash.'),
(388, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-03', 'Five Stars Coffee stays nice and hot.  I invested in this coffee maker and so happy I did.'),
(389, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Easy and quick! This is my first Keurig and it\'s fantastic! I\'ve owned a Nespresso machine, but the cups were really expensive in comparison. This machine is super quick to start and heat up the water. When the basin is low, it\'ll tell you and a light will flash in the basin until you\'ve filled it to the proper level. The entire machine is self explanatory and required very little reference on the instruction sheets provided. Enjoy it!'),
(390, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-28', 'True Best Value! Have used it for over a year. By far the most convenient and best tasting coffee maker we have ever used.  The price makes it a true Best Value!'),
(391, 5, 1, 2, '2015-06-10', 'Take A Pass Very disappointed in quality of coffee maker. I like a hot cup of coffee and usually have to heat coffee in micro wave after brewing. I also have coffee grounds at the bottom of the pot. I\'ll never again buy a Hamilton Beach Coffee Maker and will soon replace the one I bought.'),
(392, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'Outstanding coffee maker It is outstanding I love it make as much coffee as I want and then not over preparing I\'m in this highly I think everyone should get them one'),
(393, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'I\'ve always loved Keurig. I use it to make the right ... Arrived prior to when they stated it would. I\'ve used it several times already. I\'ve always loved Keurig. I use it to make the right amount of hot water for my oatmeal in the morning as well'),
(394, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-12', 'A breakfast staple These are great for making chocolate peanut butter protein shakes every morning.  They are my favorite breakfast item that fills me up for approximately 3 hours.  The one thing wrong with this product is I need to buy a new one every 6-9 months, because the base stops working.  That stinks when I have to eat a non-blended drink on a morning on which I have to work.  Fortunately, this blender is cheap and quiet.'),
(395, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-26', 'Five Stars good item  fast delivery.'),
(396, 11, 1, 5, '2015-01-02', 'I really like this toaster oven I really like this toaster oven. It is large enough to fit just about anything you would like but not so large that it overtakes your counter. The toaster oven heats up easily and appears to heat to the correct temperature. I use mine from toasting english muffins to roasting chickpeas to making mini cookies and the oven handles all of this easily. The parts are easy to clean and usually just require a quick wipe with a wet cloth.'),
(397, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-31', 'Product lives up to its name Been a great toaster and very easy to operate and manipulate.  The nice feature is that the settings are very accurate and reliable.'),
(398, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-30', 'Easy to use Easy to use.  The amount remaining indicator is really great.  It keeps  coffee warm for a reasonable time - but not hot.  I am sure that the water filter helps make the coffee taste better.'),
(399, 6, 1, 5, '2014-06-09', 'love it Very nice toaster!!! I trust Cuisinart products and this toaster is another reason why I bought this toaster! Very happy'),
(400, 11, 1, 4, '2014-10-18', 'Bigger and better than your average toaster oven Bigger and better than your average toaster oven, but not too big to overwhelm your kitchen counter space. I like that the settings around the dials are clear and legible. Not only does this toaster oven rule for toast, bagels, english muffins etc.., it\'s also excellent at reheating pizza and cooking other toaster oven suitable items with ease it\'s larger capacity inside. The plug is a 3 prong plug that protrudes slightly more than other kitchen appliance plugs and the cord could be a little longer, but we\'re very happy with this purchase. It\'s great quality for the price.'),
(401, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-08', 'A Very Good Coffeemaker by Hamilton Beach After my last two coffeemakers of a different brand died after about a year each of service I decided to purchase this Hamilton Beach and I must say that I definitely do not regret that decision. Aside from this coffeemaker being attractive, simple to operate and consistently making a good cup of coffee. Other features that I like include:   Front access to coffee ground basket   The detachable water reservoir for easy filling and cleaning   The ability to control the units hot plate temperature   Three brew settings ... Regular, 1-4 cup and Bold   Easy to understand controls   Easy set up for an automatic brew   Wheeled base making it easy to move around the counter   A decanter that does not dribble when pouring coffee Features that I dislike: No Things to be aware of: On the top of the unit is a vent to allow steam to be released as coffee is being brewed. Be aware that that portion of the unit becomes extremely hot to the point of scalding. Therefore if the coffeemaker is placed under a low cabinet you may want to pull it out while coffee is brewing to prevent damage to the cabin Update 2/16/2015 Well in the past year this coffee maker has had to preform at least once every day and has done so without fail. However this past two weeks at about every 3rd brew it shuts down at about 8 cups of a 12 cup brew ... it looses the time and stops the brew until the time is reset and the start button is once again pushed. One year without a problem works out to about eleven cents a brew or less than one cent per cup for this $40 coffee maker. I had hoped that it would have lasted longer but all things considered I still rate it 5 star and I\'m ordering a new one as I found the first to be a good coffee maker as well as a good deal plus I like its look. A Bonus for me ... I will now have a replacement cravat should I break the first.'),
(402, 9, 1, 1, '2015-05-18', 'We really liked this coffee maker at first We really liked this coffee maker at first... Until it started spraying water out of the top. The problem is the water lifts the top of the maker off making a watery mess and having a cup full of coffee in your cup. Disappointed for the price we paid'),
(403, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'Five Stars great product fast delivery thanks'),
(404, 7, 3, 2, '2015-02-21', 'I purchased this coffee maker to use in our 5th wheel trailer. It didn\'t work with the K cups that I use in my Keurig coffee maker. Also, it\'s VERY slow heating the water. So, I took it back to the store. (It \"may\" work O.K. with regular ground coffee. I didn\'t try that.)'),
(405, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-14', 'Five Stars Really good machine! So convenient and easy to use!'),
(406, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'LOVE IT! got my new keurig 2.0 brewer. LOVE IT!! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. It\'s so easy to operate. I really like the versatility of this machine. You can make a pot of coffee, a mug, or several different size cups of coffee. I just love it. I got a red one love the color.'),
(407, 10, 1, 1, '2015-07-24', 'I then bought a Nutri bullet blender and I am very happy. This item came with a 2 prong USA plug. I bought several universal conversion adaptors which did not fit it. I then took it to an electrical shop to get an adaptor to fit it. I was informed that the voltage was higher than usual uk blenders, there was not an adaptor to fit the fla 2 prong plug,and I then to it to my local dump and disposed of it as by then I was so tired of trying to actually use it. I then bought a Nutri bullet blender and I am very happy.'),
(408, 11, 1, 2, '2014-04-08', 'Toaster Too small to be useful. Meatloaf pan doesn\'t even fit in it. Get a bigger toaster oven that has a larger capaciry.'),
(409, 2, 1, 3, '2016-10-24', 'the least expensive of the black and decker toaster oven---and ... the least expensive of the black and decker toaster oven---and accordingly not nearly as well made as a higher price one I would not purchase again.'),
(410, 9, 1, 2, '2016-10-03', 'which makes this bad review all the more painful to write Beatutiful design and product, which makes this bad review all the more painful to write. The darn thing keeps leaking coffee everywhere when it brews! Set it to brew and when I returned coffee leaked all over our counter tops! Going to return it because I don\'t want to deal with the hassle of 1) finding the serial number and registering 2.) paying for shipping and handling 3.) taking a risk of having another one. Real shame :(...sorry Cuisinart!.'),
(411, 11, 1, 1, '2014-08-12', 'Worst heating mechanism! Don\'t know whether mine is defective or not however it takes forever to cook anything!  The conventional oven does not work!!!!  It takes 30 minutes to heat frozen waffles, 90 minutes to roast carrots!'),
(412, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-25', 'Five Stars Meets my expectations'),
(413, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-18', 'Four Stars works well, would give it 5 stars if it had a timer'),
(414, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-28', 'Five Stars Great!'),
(415, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-30', 'In 10 tries with K-cups it managed to make coffee twice. The rest of the time it simply went around the K-cup. Tried coffee grinds once and it spit the grounds in the cup and along the front of the machine. A terrible buy.'),
(416, 5, 1, 4, '2015-04-05', 'Four Stars So far it is working good but the product itself seems a little on the cheap side.'),
(417, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-02', 'Four Stars Works fine, smaller than I thought it would be.'),
(418, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'My Keurig 2.0 k200 I love my Keurig. My husband and I have talked about purchasing one for a few years now. There was a great sale through Bestbuy.com so I seized the opportunity and finally bought a Keurig. We love it! My only 2 complaints are that I wish that the coffee sizes were a little bigger. It seems like 10 oz should be more then a half of a cup. Also, my brewer seems to clog up after 2 uses. We have to clean the dispenser out after every 2 uses or we waste a kcup because it doesn\'t dispense correctly. It\'s not hard to clean but kind of annoying. Other then that, I love, love my Keurig!! Thanks Keurig for the free kcups for writing this review!'),
(419, 12, 1, 4, '2014-06-03', 'Useful and reliable I\'ve had this toaster for 3 years and never had any problems with it. Good toaster which pretty cool toaster/oven feature.'),
(420, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-14', 'One of the best coffeemakers I have ever owned One of the best coffeemakers I have ever owned and I have owned plenty. What is especially nice is the easy access to the water fill which allows you to see how much you\'ve added (you see it on the pot too). It cleans nice and makes a nice cup of java.'),
(421, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-29', 'Have a cup Works great'),
(422, 9, 1, 1, '2017-01-25', 'Died in just 11 months This was my second unit, Amazon replaced the first one because it was brewing Luke warm coffee. After getting this replacement I learned it only makes like warm coffee. I settled with that fact and since I use hot milk I figure I will microwave it together. Things went on fine until this morning, when I tried to brew a cup and it refused to power on. I do not drink coffee everyday and probably used this no more than 75-80 times inlays 11 months. I don\'t want to pay for shipping so it will go in trash.'),
(423, 3, 1, 1, '2014-10-13', 'Two problems - heat and labels Two problems It does get very hot on the outside, but you can probably live with that. What is worse is that the labels wear off leaving you with unlabeled buttons. This really isn\'t good. They offered no help except to tell me that using labels from a label maker wouldn\'t work because the outside gets too hot. They actually said \"it gets as hot on the outside as it gets on the inside.\" That isn\'t true. They were willing to replace the oven if you call within the warranty period (two years).'),
(424, 11, 1, 5, '2015-06-28', 'Five Stars Given as a gift.'),
(425, 6, 1, 4, '2016-07-12', 'Nice Capacity and Options Bought this to replace an inexpensive toaster that pooped out after very little use. I like the large slots and the variety of settings. Doesn\'t toast perfectly evenly, but does the job. Crumb tray easy to remove for cleaning. I trust Cuisinart in my kitchen.'),
(426, 5, 1, 2, '2016-09-10', 'Faulty Control Panel Bezel Makes good coffee, but like others, I had the bezel for the control panel fall off within a week. Ordered a replacement, but it had the same issue right out of the box. Returning this one as well now and buying something else.'),
(427, 4, 1, 2, '2015-11-06', 'All kinds of wrong with this thing The heating element warped after about a year. When baking, it makes a very loud, periodic clicking noise. This is the third one we\'ve had (we keep bringing it back to Bed Bath and Beyond, and they give us a new one, no questions asked!). The door kept sticking on the first one, second one we brought back because of the clicking, and we are about to bring the third one back because of the warping. And the clicking. Honestly, I\'m ready to bag this thing altogether and find a better unit.'),
(428, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-07', 'Five Stars good item and fast shipping'),
(429, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Thanks, Keurig I love this system Love my Keuring and have had no problems with it.  We work different schedules so no one has to drink stale coffee anymore!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(430, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-06', 'Five Stars nice looking and roomy'),
(431, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-23', 'Very Discourged!! I bought this 3 years ago and it has decided to stop working.  My warranty is up and I am very disappointed. For the price I paid it didn\'t last very long.  It worked well when I did use it.  I would never pay this much for a toaster oven again.  If I were to send it back I could buy another for the amount of postage it would cost.'),
(432, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-14', 'Five Stars Fabulous oven at a great price!'),
(433, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-17', 'Great! Perfect for what I need. I make my shakeology with almond milk and a banana. Haven\'t experienced the burning smell mentioned, but it doesn\'t take very long to blend. :)'),
(434, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-20', 'Great little coffeemaker I bought this coffeemaker three years ago because I was starting a new job that I had to be up really early for and I wanted to replace my Melitta cone with an automatic coffeemaker to make my morning routine go by a little faster. Because of the low price tag, I wasn\'t expecting it to last past the end of my summer job, but now, three years later it\'s still going strong. I use it anywhere between 1 and 3 times a day, meaning I\'ve made hundreds and hundreds of cups of coffee with this cheap little coffeemaker and it honestly makes fine coffee. My only complaint is that if you let it sit the coffee tastes burnt a lot faster than more expensive coffeemakers I\'ve used. Overall, a great little coffeemaker and the perfect size if there\'s only one coffee drinker in the house.'),
(435, 1, 1, 1, '2016-06-08', 'BEWARE! What you don\'t find out until you TRY to brew your first cup, is that there is a camera inside this coffee-maker and you must use keruig cups that come in a box with a \"circle with a checkmark in it\" or they won\'t work, even if they say keurig on  them.  You get an \"oops!\" message. I called their toll free number and was told \"only keurig cups with a \"circle and a checkmark on the packaging\" will work, and offered to send me a coupon to replace the ones I have. Thought I would have no problems because it was a Keurig, wrong!  Now looking for the \"correct cups\".  Would never have purchased it but returning it would be tough,  I didn\'t know until I set it all up.  Would not be able to package it to return it.'),
(436, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-05', 'Five Stars love it'),
(437, 9, 1, 1, '2015-11-24', 'Wouldn\'t purchase Returned. Made only lukewarm coffee; not like the Cuisinarts in the past. Also, didn\'t like the dispensing facet.'),
(438, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'We love it. It toasts bagels We love it. It toasts bagels,english muffins great. It broils great also. the timer and number settings is a big plus in comparison to our old toaster. It also re-heats leftover pizza that geats a crispy crust instead of the soggy one when you microwave it. We have not used the convection part yet. will return when we do.'),
(439, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-25', 'It works! We should have disposed of our old toaster years ago. This one actually toasts bread. Amazing!'),
(440, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-20', 'Great oven. Bought this for my son\'s first apartment Great oven.  Bought this for my son\'s first apartment.  He loves it.'),
(441, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-07', 'great toaster/oven Best toaster/oven I ever purchased. I love that the toaster top closes when you are finished.'),
(442, 12, 1, 1, '2015-03-21', 'Only good to warm a flat piece of pizza kind of a waste of money, you have to flip your toast over and retoast it because it only toast the bottom .75 and the top quarter is still bread and when your using the oven part the opening is only large enough to put in a slice of pizza..... the opening is far smaller than what the picture appears.'),
(443, 3, 1, 1, '2015-08-10', 'more crap I went thru two black&decker models and they never heated properly. The 1st one (Black & Decker TO3210SSD) didnt cook my 12\" pizza all the way and so I bought a oven thermometer. Sure enough, highest it got was 400, not 450 as stated in product info. This model was my 2nd try, said it was heated to 450 on the screen display, but it wasnt...it only reached 425 yet again. I used TWO oven thermometers just to be sure! On top of it, the buttons on this model get pretty hot to the touch. Sent both back and ended up with the Oster TSSTTVMNDG.'),
(444, 2, 1, 2, '2016-02-14', 'Two Stars A bit complex and doesn\'t seem to work like it should. You really only need to two knobs.'),
(445, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'Excellent Toaster Great toaster. It takes a bit getting used to with all the fancy buttons - BUT - it does a great job.Even the defrost button did a good job! I have no complaints and I hope it lasts a long time. I recommend it, especially if you have a little shortage of counter space...'),
(446, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-24', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker, Great price!'),
(447, 8, 1, 5, '2014-02-24', 'black & decker stuff rocks works great very happy with it I use it every morning I am sold on black & decker aplinces thanks'),
(448, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-08', 'EASY WAY TO PUT WATER IN! Bought this for my wife to replace another brand that stopped working.  She really loves the easy reservoir for put water in.  The coffee maker works very well.'),
(449, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-20', 'Great Coffee Maker Easy to use; works perfectly. Highly recommend.'),
(450, 10, 1, 3, '2015-01-23', 'kinda noisy and the lid has a spillage i wouldnt ... kinda noisy and the lid has a spillage i wouldnt leave it in my bag maybe a side pocket'),
(451, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-27', 'Elements We love this toaster except they last only about 2 years.'),
(452, 5, 1, 1, '2014-03-29', 'Bitter coffee Makes bitter coffee. The first pot I made tasted bitter so I made another pot. Still bitter. Bought new bag of coffee. Made a third pot. Bitter. Made side by side comparison with a cheap black and decker coffee make I had a work. The black and decker made better coffee. Packaged this coffee maker and sent it back. Loved the removable reservoir for cleaning.'),
(453, 9, 1, 4, '2016-09-06', 'Happy overall. I am happy with this coffee maker for the most part. I do wish it had a bold brew option. Also a regular sized travel mug requires you to remove the drip tray to fill. This is ok, but an inconvenience.'),
(454, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-08', 'Pretty good! Good quality for the price. I have to take the cup off and shake it around a few times to blend everything, but not bad considering it\'s only $15 and others cost about $80 if not more.'),
(455, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-10', 'Five Stars Cant go wrong with B&D'),
(456, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-14', 'I use it almost every day and it works wonderfully! My teenage sons enjoy using this oven too I\'ve had my Cuisienart Custom Classic Toaster Oven for a while now. I use it almost every day and it works wonderfully!  My teenage sons enjoy using this oven too. Very convenient.'),
(457, 12, 1, 5, '2014-02-03', 'Little red toaster oven Works just as described.  This is a small oven but perfect for my needs.  I have used it for baking pot pies and other small items.  Two slices of pizza will fit.  It heats up quickly.  I do not usually like anything out on my counters but this takes so little space and looks great.'),
(458, 4, 1, 1, '2015-06-24', 'DANGEROUS FIRE HAZARD - Does NOT turn off Bought this a year and a half ago. It gets minimal use since it is in a vacation home. The off switch just stopped working so it is not possible to turn the heating elements off. This is a fire hazard. A user can push the off button, thinking they turned the oven off, and the heating elements continue heating the oven indefinitely. The oven is not well insulated so can overheat when this happens and cause a house fire.  Amazon won\'t take it back or replace it because they only guarantee it for a month. Update - I called Amazon and asked if they would refund my purchase price so that I could buy another brand, or provide me a replacement of another brand. I said I didn\'t want to go through the Cuisinart replacement program, because this item is a documented fire hazard (read other reviews), and I don\'t want another one in my home. They said they could not do this since it was outside the one month purchase window. They acknowledged they are aware it is a fire hazard but are unwilling to provide a refund.  They did say they would take this off their sell list until they could look further into the fire danger issue. Glad to see they are looking out for Amazon, and trying to protect themselves against litigation, but not looking out for their customers by providing refunds or replacements of another brand. This is disappointing and not very Amazon like. From now on I will buy electronics/appliances elsewhere.'),
(459, 5, 1, 4, '2014-07-13', 'Good coffee pot. A nice coffee pot. Works quite well and is easy to use.'),
(460, 6, 1, 1, '2015-01-26', 'One Star toasts one side well done and the other very light.'),
(461, 11, 1, 3, '2016-09-23', 'Three Stars Have to give it three stars as I am still getting used to it.p.'),
(462, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-19', 'Keurig for single cup or pot! Love this machine.  I tried the Hamilton Beach maker that is supposed to make individual cups as well as a pot.  I went through 3 of them in a year because it kept locking up on me when I tried to go back and forth between individual vs. pot. This Keurig has been a blessing.  I run a cup of hot water through the machine about every 6th cup, just to keep things clean and running well.  I\'ve also used the larger pods to make a pot. Very impressed. I have the smaller of the two multi-function brewers and it does the job for me.'),
(463, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-21', 'One Star Only used this product 2 times and it broke. I am highly disappointed'),
(464, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-29', 'Wish I could say I haven\'t made this mistake before I rarely use this style of coffee maker anymore and although I am an educated adult woman with a brain I didn\'t realize that this was a tiny coffee pot. It\'s good for someone who doesn\'t want to make more than, say, 5 cups.'),
(465, 12, 1, 4, '2015-04-05', 'Double duty toaster This is a versatile reasonably priced product'),
(466, 5, 1, 3, '2016-02-26', 'Amazon was great. gave me the option to return/exchange but since ... the top part of the face plate fell off after having it for less than a week. krazy glued it back in place. Amazon was great. gave me the option to return/exchange but since it was a just cosmetic issue they offered to refund 25% if I decided to keep it which was great cuz I didn\'t feel like going through the who thing with reboxing it and dropping it off to post etc. makes a good pot of coffee!'),
(467, 6, 1, 4, '2016-12-16', 'Spend the extra $5 it\'s worth it I\'ve had it a month and it doesn\'t throw the toast out and seems to toast to the level it is set (both firsts for me in a toaster).'),
(468, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-01', 'Great product.  One recommendation. Great coffee maker.  We like strong coffee and this machine puts enough water through to brew well.  It could be a little taller so that tall cups could fit under without pulling out the drip tray.  Overall great value.'),
(469, 4, 1, 2, '2016-10-10', 'Great until the heating elements brake. Worked fine until the lower heating elements broke.  Apparently this cannot be repaired.  Bad design.'),
(470, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-16', 'fits a standard 9x11 baking pan! (the types without handles) This toaster oven is awesome... Bakes, toasts, broils, and cooks a 12\" pizza to perfection (all preset functions that are adjustable).  The only thing I wish The company would do is make a reference guide on the oven for the correct rack position to use when using the oven. Otherwise it takes some experimentation to get it functioning properly (or you could reference the instructions, which can be an inconvenience). It does get really hot, but it doesn\'t come across as a problem for me. To say the least... Great little baking machine (nothing bigger than a decent size chicken)'),
(471, 8, 1, 5, '2015-10-25', 'Top quality product This coffee maker is a wonderful product for an exceptionally great price. It makes a great cup of coffee with out costing a ridiculous amount of money at the coffee shop or for the machine itself. The top part holds the coffee filters really well, is easy to clean out, and doesn\'t feel flimsy. The water tank is also well made and holds a lot of water. The pot is made out of glass and both feels solid and fits in the machine really well.'),
(472, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Five Stars Perfect and just the right size'),
(473, 9, 1, 4, '2015-04-30', 'Works fine so far What you would expect. Works fine so far. 3 year warranty..'),
(474, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-30', 'Five Stars Great product & awesome price'),
(475, 7, 3, 4, '2015-12-11', 'I bought this because it did not require the K cups. I use typical ground coffee and it seems to work fine.'),
(476, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-29', 'Great product So far so good.  I love the option of baking small batches of cookies in this, or even a caserolle.'),
(477, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-19', 'great size! and works perfectly great size!  and works perfectly.'),
(478, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-21', 'A nice addition to the kitchen A good looking toaster and a variety of selections.  Also, a great price!'),
(479, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Five Stars It\'s been several years since I had a toaster oven. The price is right.'),
(480, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Best machine for the active family This is our third Keurig and it did not disappoint us at all.  The ability to use one machine for a cup or a carafe is ideal for our lifestyle since the wife\'s work hours are variable and her schedules change.  The quality of the brewer is another reason we chose to invest in another one.  I actually ended up taking our other Keurig to my office to use there.  The ability to change to different brews or even different types of drinks makes this one of the best choices for having friends over too.  No more worrying about whether or not you can please everyone\'s pallet.  All you need is a variety of pods and you are all set.  I highly recommend this brewer to anyone who wants to be able to enjoy the ability to brew different drinks with one machine.  I received product/compensation for my unbiased review.'),
(481, 5, 1, 4, '2015-12-30', 'Almost perfect I like everything about this except that the front panel cover keeps coming off and has to be snapped back on.  I guess it\'s just not worth it to me to return since i like it otherwise, but that is the reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5. It\'s attractive and I like being able to remove the water reservoir to fill it.  Also the pause feature actually works; I find so often these don\'t and you end up with coffee leaking onto the burner. There is an automatic turn off feature which is important to me.  Except for that panel cover, it\'s a perfect coffee pot and the stainless steel design matches my other appliances.'),
(482, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-16', 'Very easy and simple to use! Bought the Keurig K250 for my dad and he loves it. Very user friendly and easy to use. He is the only one who drinks coffee so he doesn\'t have to worry about brewing a whole batch of coffee in the morning. He simply pushes the button and then gets ready for work, when he gets back theres a fresh cup of coffee made. The only downside is the sensor which only allows Keurig approved k-cups, there\'s a few different hacks to get around this so it works with any k-cup.'),
(483, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-20', 'works few months now, no problems with blender.'),
(484, 12, 1, 5, '2014-07-07', 'Five Stars Its highly recommend.'),
(485, 4, 1, 1, '2015-09-16', 'One Star it broke after 3 months'),
(486, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-08', 'Five Stars Love this toaster'),
(487, 11, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'Good toaster oven! I bought this to have at work upstairs in the office for everyone to use. It\'a a really good toaster oven. It was a great price and works really well. Everyone likes it. It\'s spacious and looks good! I\'d recommend it!'),
(488, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-31', 'Five Stars Fine.'),
(489, 8, 1, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Everyday use my daughter gave it to her boyfriend for a birthday present and he loves it. He uses it everyday.'),
(490, 11, 1, 3, '2015-01-19', 'Low quality oven So damn tiny and the timer only goes to 20 minutes.  If you\'re toasting bread it works great.  I have been using this since my oven broke and find I can\'t use it for as much as I\'d hoped.  However, for the price you can still heat a frozen pizza (as long as you cut it in sections first!)'),
(491, 12, 1, 5, '2014-07-18', 'Five Stars Gorgeous to look at!!'),
(492, 5, 1, 1, '2014-05-13', 'Died within 3 months It seemed to be a decent coffee maker while it lasted... which wasn\'t long.  I just went to make my coffee this morning, and after I hit the ON switch, nothing happened. I tried readjusted the carafe, basket, etc., making sure the hatches were all firmly closed.  I even tried plugging the machine in to a different electrical outlet (even though the outlet worked fine for the other item plugged into it). Bottom line: this HB coffee maker simply up and died after 2-1/2 months.  Conveniently just past the return window, I might add.  Luckily, amazon still allowed me to return it for a refund. But I wouldn\'t buy this thing again.'),
(493, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-23', 'good This toaster oven is great. It is mostly black with stainless trim. It\'s looks pretty on the counter and has a whole lot of options on the knobs for heating. Comes with everything shown. The top, side and door do get very hot to the touch, so use with care.'),
(494, 5, 1, 1, '2016-11-10', 'Loud and long brew time. This was the worse coffee maker I ever did own. It was very loud and took up to 45 minutes to fully brew a pot of coffee. We had to move it to a bedroom on the other side of the house and close the door so it would not wake us up while brewing for 45 minutes. It\'s gone to the great recycle yard in the sky.'),
(495, 5, 1, 1, '2015-03-01', 'It made great coffee and was easy to use Purchased this Coffee maker a year and a half ago and did not put it into service for almost a year.  It made great coffee and was easy to use.  However, less than six months into using it, it went totally dead.  Because it was long out of warranty, it was not even worth calling Hamilton Beach about.  Have read too many reviews describing the same set of circumstances.  It is a sad commentary about a once great company that they now seemingly routinely produce a product that only lasts half a year in actual use.  My late Mother\'s Hamilton Beach Mixer is still running sixty five years after she got it as a wedding present.  Maybe if they considered bringing production of their products back to the United States they might yet again become a great company. I cannot recommend this product to anyone with any degree of confidence.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(496, 9, 1, 1, '2015-03-11', 'Nice looking but poor choice for me I give it stars for looks. I\'ve had this coffee maker for 2 weeks and am still working on perfecting a good cup of coffee. First, there is no way to tell when the water is \'ready.\'  You have to turn it on/off to get it to hear the new water if you\'ve cleaned it out. Second, you can\'t just fill the water and then use the amount if grinds you want per cup. Third, day 14 and the water leaked everywhere. UPDATE: don\'t think I\'ll be buying from Cuisinart again. Coffee maker a dud. Sprays coffee everywhere. Obviously a lemon. Called the company. I am being charged $10 to have them ship me a new one and then I am paying for return postage. So the $100 coffee maker, that was under warranty and never worked, cost me  $125.'),
(497, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-29', 'Five Stars So far so good! Quick and easy'),
(498, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', '0 system I had never used one before so I thought I would give it a shot I couldn\'t believe how easy it was how good the coffee I visited a friend that lives in New Port Richy Fla for a few days the first morning I saw that he had a Keurig 2.0 system I had never used one before so I thought I would give it a shot I couldn\'t believe how easy it was how good the coffee was when I got home the first thing I did I went to walmart and purchased a Kurig K250 2.0 Brewing system and I love it thanks for reading'),
(499, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'works great can bake for two easily,pizza, cake,etc.'),
(500, 11, 1, 1, '2015-02-06', 'Too bad. In my entire married life I\'ve owned only ... Update to this previous review...I still stand by the following information on this specific B&D oven, but I want to give a shoutout to Spectrum Brands who read this review and reached out to me to make sure I got my money back - thank you for good customer service! Too bad. In my entire married life I\'ve owned only 2 Black & Decker ovens which really did their jobs for about 13 years each!  So, of course, when the last one gave out, there was no question of what I would buy again. Right away, however, I realized this one was not living up to that standard and I was so disappointed.  Difficult to use controls don\'t allow you to find your perfect setting and leave it and worse, because of this it was prone to catch fire! I finally got the time to call Amazon to return it, but had missed their return window so I was stuck with it. Amazon suggested I contact Black & Decker, but after looking on Black & Decker\'s own sight at recent customer ratings for all of their toaster ovens, I think Black & Decker needs to do some serious customer interface and quality control work to get back the reputation their previous ovens garnered for them. I didn\'t see a product on there with a high enough rating that they could send me in place of this one and I doubt they\'d give me my money back, so right now, I\'m using one of those $5 loss-leader toasters they sell around Christmas &, ironically, it\'s much better.'),
(501, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-03', '10/10 IGN Never had a toaster oven before and I\'m glad I finally bit the bullet and got one. I wasn\'t disappointed with this one either. This toaster oven is rather small inside and what I mean by that is you wont be putting any turkeys or chickens in here. If however you wish to bake a few cookies or a helping of fries or toast a couple bagels, even corn dogs come out perfectly. And oh yeah it makes toast too ;) (Already have a toaster so not gonna use this feature that much unless I want to melt the butter on my toast or warm up soggy toast. Cuz who likes soggy toast)'),
(502, 8, 1, 4, '2014-06-29', 'Easy to clean Works well and quickly.  Easy to clean.'),
(503, 11, 1, 1, '2014-06-18', 'Poor design causes rack to tip, leads to hand burns. When you slide out the wire rack, it tips down and the rack and what was on it slides out until it is stopped by your utensil, oven mitt, or possibly, your hand.  When did they lay off the engineers that designed earlier, safe, models? Rack tipping, or rack dump, is causes by using a straight, narrow guage wire rack sliding too wide a stamped steel slot.  Cheapest fix is to add v dimples on the rack slides to make it seem fatter. Black and decker appliances used to be good.  Are now poorly designed.'),
(504, 7, 3, 3, '2014-01-16', 'this was a Christmas gift and so far I have gone through 1 box of K-cups. I have also brewed coffee using my own grounds. I did get some of the grounds at the bottom of the mug. I did use finely ground coffee even though the instructions say not to so Im sure this was the reason for the grounds in my mug. I have 3 issues with this machine. While brewing the coffee does splash out of the mug a bit, when filling the reservoir it does drain slowly into the tank and if I try to brew another cup right after the first cup the machine seems to brew the coffee while pouring the water into the reservior even with the machine turned off(very strange). Besides those 3 issues the machine brews a great cup of coffee, I like the flex brew option and that you can use a travel mug or a standard mug.'),
(505, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Great buy Absolutely love my brewer. It is perfect for my college dorm! Occasionally have issues with it sensing my cups but still works well!'),
(506, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-26', 'Brewer went bad after five weeks Brewer went bad after five weeks...it constantly says \"Reheating\".  I tried descaling the brewer using the Keurig descaling solution. Still no change.  I have a $150 doorstop sitting on my kitchen counter.  I missed the return window with the Amazon selling system by only two days.  Now I have to deal with Keurig directly...they are not helpful either.'),
(507, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-24', 'works great just what I wanted'),
(508, 7, 3, 4, '2014-05-04', 'I like the fact you can use either k-cups or ground coffee. Works great on either coffee.'),
(509, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'This is a fun little coffee maker. This is a fun little coffee maker for those that don\'t need a 12 cup pot. I recommend this..'),
(510, 6, 1, 4, '2016-05-08', 'Toasters are all so disappointing. None seem to be ... Toasters are all so disappointing. None seem to be able to toast evenly or unevenly consistently. Sure we can pay a higher price for a brand name plastic chassis but on the inside is the same cheap little teensy wires attached to cardboard. The only reason to buy this one over a lesser brand is the lift-up feature that raises to toast up high enough to grab it without burning. That rates a star!'),
(511, 4, 1, 5, '2016-11-14', 'Five Stars Everything I expected...thank you.'),
(512, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(513, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'Very Pleased with Hamilton Beach! Makes a great pot of coffee!! I love the way this thing works. It\'s super easy to use & has a digital clock which is a plus. Definitely an upgrade from my last coffee maker! I love the auto-brew feature. It\'s great for those who like to make their coffee ahead of time before bed and have it ready for them when they wake up. You can adjust so much on this coffee maker- it honestly has features I didn\'t even know existed & it\'s made life easier, for sure. You can adjust the speed of the brew. You literally have a say in how strong your coffee comes through! As most coffee makers have nowadays, it has the auto shut off for the mornings you rush out the door and forget to turn it off. I LOVE the water reservoir. It comes off so you can fill it in the sink or with the water from your refrigerator door. So nice! Overall, an amazing product. I\'m really impressed.'),
(514, 12, 1, 5, '2015-03-24', '7 YEARS AWESOME!!! Bought 4 units- Best kitchen purchase I\'ve made in my bi-coastal properties AND for my adult children for their new apartments. Saves on space , looks stylish , and does a wonderful job. My housekeeper dropped my original Hamilton beach toaster oven breaking it which I immeduately replaced with the same unit- that was 7 years ago! Awesome find. You\'ll love your waffles, toast and pizza'),
(515, 12, 1, 3, '2015-05-14', 'Don\'t buy unless u plan on not using it When cooking on the inside it caught on fire real easy and burnt up real fast'),
(516, 7, 3, 4, '2016-07-07', 'It works really well, I\'m glad I purchased this.'),
(517, 12, 1, 4, '2017-01-20', 'Four Stars Works well.'),
(518, 3, 1, 1, '2016-08-18', 'One Star Received damaged and returned it.'),
(519, 6, 1, 2, '2015-02-13', 'Think twice- my version of this toaster doesn\'t toast well at all I love the Cuisinart brand, that said, this particular toaster just doesn\'t work.  I\'ve been using for 3 weeks daily to toast English muffins and cannot seem to get the muffins to brown, even though I have the dial set up to 6.  This is not usual for cuisinart, but I\'m disappointed at having spent the money for something that doesn\'t work.'),
(520, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-24', 'Works great so far. I bought this toaster oven so that I could cook brats and sausages in it. I usually only cook 2-4 sausages at a time and don\'t want to turn on my big oven just for that small amount so I bought this little toaster oven for that purpose. So far they have come out perfectly fine. I usually cook brats in my regular oven at 400 degrees for about 30 minutes and they are perfect. With this toaster oven, I have to set the heat a little higher (450 degrees) but it comes out the same in 30 minutes. I\'m happy. Now I don\'t have to turn on my huge oven just to cook a few sausages.'),
(521, 4, 1, 5, '2016-10-13', 'Five Stars Love it.'),
(522, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-23', 'Would not buy again. use it everyday. great for smoothies. After 60 days mine died.  Motor too small. Upgraded to more powerful unit.'),
(523, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-17', 'Best Tasting Coffee Works great. These just seem to make better tasting coffee than other types we\'ve tried.  I like the light for the cup area.  Easy to clean. We had a DCC-2000 that only lasted a few years.  Hope this one lasts longer.'),
(524, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-02', 'Great product Great coffee maker. I really like the fact it has a auto on auto off features.  The carafe feature is also wonderful. Has a large well for water so you don\'t have to full the well everyday. The only thing I don\'t like is not being able to use my own coffee. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(525, 5, 1, 4, '2014-05-21', 'Performs as described It\'s a good value Have used it for one month and no performance issues Coffee is hot and the various options are useful The translucent heavy plastic lift off water reservoir looks kind of cheap but actually seems well made Glad I got it'),
(526, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-06', 'Five Stars I\'m very pleased with this coffee maker.'),
(527, 11, 1, 1, '2014-12-30', 'Hate it I need to return it Why don\'t they ... Hate it I need to return it Why don\'t they make toast ovens like they used to This is the 2nd Black and Decker toaster oven I have purchased this year They are flimsy junk Where o where can I get a sturdy toaster oven that doesn\'t take over your whole cupboard Keep me posted'),
(528, 3, 1, 2, '2014-08-02', 'I would have opted not to purchase knowing what I know now. Yeah, I would not buy this again.  First of all, it takes up a huge amount of space on the counter, even though I measured before buying - it just seems bigger than I had expected.  It gets dirty really fast and easily and I cannot get the top clean no matter what kind of cleaning products I use.  It is designed in a way that the display screen is digital.  Not a problem.  BUT, the blue light flashes when  you are choosing your settings making it nearly impossible to see the digital screen!!!  You have to practically use a flashlight to maintain clarity of the digital screen while the poorly placed flashing blue light blinks out of control.  So not worth the money.  It is supposed to be a convection oven and I think that the convection feature works - but it cooks unevenly - anything placed in the back of the oven pan/rack burns while the items in the front towards the glass door are only halfway there.'),
(529, 6, 1, 1, '2016-04-11', 'We just got our second unit. This one did ... We just got our second unit. This one did not even take two months to break. It was broken out of the box. The control that you push down for to toast will not stay down. Also, even when it worked, you had to pull out the toast and turn it around for even toasting. The Cuisinart name used to mean something. Now it means the lowest price junk you can find. They figured they would make more money with their name than by producing quality products. Do not buy this product. Other Cuisinart products have had similar quality problems. (Have a toaster oven that is also useless).'),
(530, 9, 1, 2, '2015-04-16', 'Didn\'t last Short life span Buy a Keurig'),
(531, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-23', 'very nice Its a very nice toaster, it works so well and I have no problems with it.'),
(532, 12, 1, 5, '2014-01-02', 'Love this Toastation Toaster Oven I love the retro style of this toaster over! I love even more, the fact that I can toast bread and then melt cheese over it in the oven with only sliding the lever over to oven!! It\'s easy to clean and performs well above my expectations/'),
(533, 9, 1, 1, '2016-02-06', 'Junk with bad customer service It is now 1 year old and has a leaking problem again. The first time customer service sent a new reservoir and then it worked for a few months.  Now it leaked 12 cups and made a bad mess. I thought it needed a new reservoir again so I called customer service again. After more than 1 hour on hold, I got to talk to a real person. She informed me that the only way to get help was for me to send it to them and I must pay postage. They will then decide on a repair and I am stuck without a coffeemaker until they ship it back at my expense. The 3 year warranty is worthless. It\'s going in the garbage. I also sent them an email explaining this problem and will update this when they answer.'),
(534, 5, 1, 5, '2016-12-16', 'Five Stars Awesome...bought this for my mother...small footprint...great coffee.'),
(535, 10, 1, 3, '2016-06-27', 'Three Stars Useful.'),
(536, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-05', 'It is a great product. I currently have the 3 It is a great product. I currently have the 3.0 and bought this one for my daughter. She loves the convenience of it.'),
(537, 2, 1, 1, '2016-09-13', 'Just doesn\'t work Do not be seduced by the amazing price. You really do it get what you pay for. It looks excellent and fits in a small space. However, it only toasts the top of the bread (the underside was completely soft). The oven rack is tilted at the lowest (most common) height. And I tried baking a potato at 400 for almost 90 minutes, and the inside was still raw while the skin was barely cooked. I have used toaster ovens for this task for over 20 years, and this one just does not work.  Have begun the return process.'),
(538, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-17', 'I\'m very satisfied with the purchase! It doesn\'t take too much of space on the countertop and it works great on reheating food n making a toast. I like using this instead of using a big conventional oven. It helps to save time n energy as well.'),
(539, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-10', 'Five Stars It is great.'),
(540, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-17', 'perfect for late night smoothies at the bar I got this for work for quick meals. Quiet, fast, perfect for late night smoothies at the bar.'),
(541, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-17', 'No beep, no fuss, just decent. The main reason I bought the 46201 - reviews indicated it doesn\'t beep.  I hate things which beep, and why should a coffee machine beep in the first place?  Like I would forget I made a pot, or that 5 minutes has passed? Fortunately, in addition to not annoying my half awake self in the morning (or those still blissfully asleep), it is also a decent machine for the money.  Brew time is not onerous at about a minute per cup, a bit longer when using \"bold\" mode. It takes about 5 minutes for the heating plate to reach full temp, so if I \"sneak\" a cup, it may not be as hot as I would like.  But if I\'m sneaking, I\'m not too concerned about temperature or full flavor in the first place (if I were, I\'d use my french press). Controls are intuitive, auto-off feature shuts down at exactly 2 hours and temp control allows you to keep things hot without cooking your coffee.  The removable water reservoir eliminates spills and the pot itself allows me to pour a cup without making a mess.  Timer seems to work as expected, although I\'ve only tested it out and haven\'t used it on a daily basis. In short, it makes a decent cup of coffee without having to think or do much. My only complaint, the LED display is a bit too bright.  I don\'t need it to serve as a clock, visable from across the kitchen.  An LCD display with minimal backlighting would have been less intrusive (another peeve - bright LEDs.  Why do manufacturers make so many appliances which beep, blink or light up a dark room?).'),
(542, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-09', 'Just great I am extremely pleased with this Toaster Over. I owned them in the past and will own them in the future. NONE BETTER'),
(543, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-29', 'Five Stars i like the bold brew feature.'),
(544, 6, 1, 1, '2014-07-29', 'To toast bread turn up to MAX TWICE then turn toast around! Cuisinart, prior experience was excellent so I ignored some of the negative reviews of this toaster.  Too late to return so I am stuck with it.  In order to toast bread it is necessary to turn it to the maximum setting TWICE and then turn the bread around to toast the other side.  Building a toaster is not rocket science so why Cuisinart cannot manage to \"build\" a workable toaster may well be testimony to the Cuisinart brand.  It is lovely on the counter but that is all it is capable of - looking nice but quite useless!'),
(545, 6, 1, 4, '2015-02-02', 'Perfect Came on time and exactly like the picture!'),
(546, 3, 1, 2, '2015-08-06', 'To be frank, I don\'t know how this product is receiving such high reviews. The construction materials used seem high quality and sleek especially for this price range. The oven also comes with great accessories as well. However, the positives stop there. The lack of functionality and the glaring hazards of this product renders it as one that\'s overdue for an update and an inconvenience in your kitchen. You immediately notice the oven\'s door - the handle\'s construction is strangely very heavy and only has a terribly weak spring to slow it down, if at all. With the added weight of the glass, opening the door is a sledge hammer-like free fall to your countertop, leaving your family to tremble in fear with every use. The buttons interface/internal program is clunky, and reminded me of the programming that goes into cheap alarm clocks. I\'d much rather have some decent knobs and simplified usability over the fancy exterior and accessory features. The oven\'s heat does not stop when you open the door, making much of the heat go directly into your kitchen and to the user. It seems dangerous and insensible to me (I later learned this is common in some other ovens too, so it may be a non-factor). Another very obvious issue for me was that the system beeps are unbearably loud and ear-piercing. At EVERY BUTTON PRESS you will be notified with an alarm clock level decibel (further drawing similarities to a cheap alarm clock). It just kind of made me laugh at how stupid it was. I was really tempted to give this product 3 stars for the overall design and materials used, but I value safety and solid operation over aesthetics. To top it off, my unit actually came with a dented top, in the top right corner. There were also some funky burning fumes that came from the initial use which gave me a headache. I had little reason not to return this product. Just a poorly executed, scarcely tested product with usage as an afterthought to good looks. It seems like an outdated machine in today\'s standards. (This experience made me scratch my head a little, and taught me to exercise caution with positive Amazon reviews - 80%+ in the positives is not free ticket to assume a smart purchase. One also has to take into account for when the reviews were written. Some aspects of this product feels like pre-2008 user experience.)'),
(547, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-04', 'Still working. still working after a year\'s heavy use ... Still working. still working after a year\'s heavy use --once a day:) The blade is not as sharp as when was new, but enough to work on small ice-cubes for my smoothie.'),
(548, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-09', 'Best. Oven. Ever. I bought this almost three years ago and it is still working beautifully. I\'ve baked pizzas, fruit pies, cookies, kale chips, and plain old toast in it and it\'s aced all of them. It heats evenly (ie no cooked in the back but raw in the front) the convection function helps things cook quickly and can serve as a drying function (for things like kale chips r frozen French fries), and it gets good and hot with the broiler function. I\'ve purchased models that are 2-3x the price and none have been as effective and long lasting as this one. By far my favorite and most frequently used kitchen appliance.'),
(549, 12, 1, 3, '2015-08-23', 'Mixed review Toasts well but smaller things sometimes get stuck. Getting food into oven js awkward but Okay for small items'),
(550, 1, 1, 4, '2016-08-26', 'But doesnt hold a whole ton of water and the whole thing feels pretty light/cheap. Otherwise looks good and does the trick Works well. But doesnt hold a whole ton of water and the whole thing feels pretty light/cheap. Otherwise looks good and does the trick.'),
(551, 2, 1, 2, '2016-02-23', 'Doesn\'t toast well Poorly designed. The dials are large and can\'t be fine-tuned, so one day your toast will be underdone and the next it\'ll be fried to a crisp.'),
(552, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Great toaster! I just wish the inside was a ... Great toaster!  I just wish the inside was a little bigger.'),
(553, 3, 1, 4, '2016-04-05', 'Four Stars great'),
(554, 2, 1, 1, '2015-11-01', 'One Star This is a toaster. The oven does not work well and takes forever.'),
(555, 3, 1, 4, '2016-08-25', 'I rarely use our gas oven and it would recommend this highly This is the 2nd Black & Decker convection oven an upgraded edition to 1 where I reluctantly retired.  I rarely use our gas oven and it would recommend this highly.'),
(556, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-20', 'Good coffee I\'ve been using this daily for 6 months and it still works great.'),
(557, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-08', 'Five Stars All good'),
(558, 5, 1, 2, '2016-03-02', 'Hami we hardly knew ya Born 4/26/15, died 2/22/16. Hamilton \"Hami\" Beach passed away in his sleep just two months short of his one year anniversary on the job. He did not report for his normal 6:15 A.M. automatic brew and could not be revived. Faulty electronics are suspected. When asked if they would replace Hami with the same model, the owners responded with a resounding \"No\".'),
(559, 1, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Awesome Our first Keurig but we love it.  Brews fast and so simple to use. Big water reservoir.'),
(560, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-29', 'Love\'n it, it\'s perfect, and the multiple ways to brew is an extra nice feature to have. It\'s small, so it doesn\'t take up much counter space.'),
(561, 12, 1, 5, '2014-07-01', 'This is my third one! I love this toaster oven and bought two more for our apartment and summer house! The toaster feature is a little quirky, but saving counter space outweighs any negatives here!'),
(562, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-09', 'Five Stars EXCELLENT TOASTER. GREAT QUALITY.'),
(563, 6, 1, 3, '2014-09-17', 'Three Stars No even toastig on both sides.'),
(564, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-03', 'Five Stars Works great!'),
(565, 9, 1, 4, '2015-07-22', 'excellent coffee maker excellent coffee maker.  brews with water at the correct temperature and the reservoir keeps the coffee hot without getting bitter. it does take up more counter space than its predecessor however and the cord is too short (@ 7\") which may limit where you put it.'),
(566, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-01', 'Five Stars great toaster with easy cleaning really like that you can have higher pop up'),
(567, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Review of Keurig 20. K-Cup brewer This is my first Keurig and bought it through a special deal with Dunkin Donuts.  I did not realize that you couldn\'t use any K-Cups in the unit.  Even some of the K-cups that they say will work in the 2.0, will not work in it.  I have had a couple of the Keurig brewed K-cups mess up in the coffee maker and make a real mess.  I did complain to Keurig about this problem after I had taken the coffee maker all apart and cleaned it like it says to do, and still was not making the cup of coffee.  They sent me a new one.  I will continue to use the coffee maker because I only drink one or two cups of coffee a day.  I wish the hot water selection would give you 8 oz instead of only 4 or 6.  I am not sure I would ever buy another one if I have to buy Keurig brand K-Cups only.  Pretty expensive for coffee, but the hot water selection is handy if you want instant.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(568, 7, 3, 4, '2014-11-15', 'Ease of use for 1-2 cups with my coffee or a treat with a different K cup.'),
(569, 10, 1, 2, '2015-02-15', 'Two Stars Excellent idea and design just that once u start using it u get a strong burning smell.'),
(570, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-29', 'Love this coffeemaker! Really like the removable water reservoir - no more spilling on the counter!  I also like the wheels so you can roll the coffeemaker back under the cabinets after filling.  Makes great coffee and I like all the timer and heater features.  Like the swivel filter basket.  I also bought the mesh filter basket so I don\'t have to mess with paper filters.  This is the best coffee maker I\'ve ever owned.  I have no dislikes about this product.  Would recommend it to anyone.'),
(571, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-14', 'Hard to go wrong with anything from Cuisinart. Easy to use.  You will have to try a couple of settings to get the toast just the way you like it.  After that, you\'re ready to go.'),
(572, 6, 1, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Toasts fine, has the lift for pieces that don\'t reach ... It\'s just what I expected.  Wanted a toaster that took up less space then our 4 slice one did.  Toasts fine, has the lift for pieces that don\'t reach to top, adjustable settings.  So far so good.'),
(573, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-22', 'however this is one of the best purchases I\'ve ever made I got this oven at a warehouse store for considerably less money, however this is one of the best purchases I\'ve ever made. My apt holds heat like you wouldn\'t believe. Even in the winter turning the oven on raises the temp at least 10 degrees. Then in the summer it\'s torture. Unbelievably hot. I found this and it\'s amazing. I will say the cord is so short it\'s absurd. Probably for safety issues, but I had to order a little baby extension cord. However this this is amazing. It takes almost no time at all to preheat. To the point where I thought there could be no way it\'s finished already. But I recommend this for anyone. It looks great, it\'s ridiculously huge and extremely easy to use. I haven\'t used all the functions yet, but it\'s like a new toy and I\'m excited to try it out! Don\'t hesitate! Buy it!'),
(574, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-30', 'Five Stars Works well even when crushing ice. It serves my portable needs.'),
(575, 8, 1, 3, '2014-08-25', 'Just OK. Couple of problems. This coffee maker is really simple and does a good job at preparing hot coffee. BUT the shower head holder broke on the FIRST use. There is not much need for the holder, so I will not pay much attention to it. The product came incomplete (without the removable filter basket that is stated in the instruction manual, page 12. Part DCM600M-FILTER. I used it with water about 5 times in order to get rid of the plastic taste but there\'s still some weird smell in it. This item is OK, but do not expect much in terms of look and quality. This is OK as an everyday coffee maker. Not a fancy piece.'),
(576, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-01', 'Five Stars Perfect___Easy to use and easy to clean.'),
(577, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Coffee maker works great. With this unit you do not have to ... Coffee maker works great. With this unit you do not have to mess around with a carafe. It is very easy to fill with water and to clean.'),
(578, 3, 1, 5, '2014-02-26', 'Outstanding I looked for quite awhile until I found this oven . It is the right size and works as I wanted. This unit has served me well for bagels, biscuits, and small casseroles .'),
(579, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-25', 'fits in small kitchen Perfect size for making one large mug and a 1/2 (5cups) Enough caffeine for one hopped up person or two coffee sippers. Makes a good cup of coffee.Usually hot enough for most people but I like mine near scalding (especially adding 1/2 and 1/2)so 1 minute in microwave. One plus is cord is long enough unlike some makers which give you this 6\" thing that just reaches.Great price-good also for the workplace.'),
(580, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-13', 'It works great and better than a conventional toaster for breads and ... It works great and better than a conventional toaster for breads and muffins.  I got fed up trying to dig bread out of the regular toasters, especially homemade breads.  This one seems to toast just fine and that\'s pretty much what I use it for.'),
(581, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-02', 'Five Stars bought it for half year, works very well'),
(582, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-30', 'Five Stars Loved this so much this one is for neighbor'),
(583, 1, 1, 3, '2015-08-25', 'Keurig K250 2.0 Review I received a Keurig 250 Brewing System as a gift on my birthday. I am pleased with the way it brews my coffee in different cup sizes and always  nice and hot the way I like it. I am disappointed, however, to find out that it doesn\'t give me the option of using refillable cups for my own coffee mix. I won\'t recommend or purchase a K250  2.0 machine for anyone else, or get another one for myself should this one fail, unless Keurig manufactures them and send some to me no charge. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(584, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-02', 'The Best Coffee Maker. The coffee pot is by far superior to the many that I have had before.  I love the water well in back of the coffee maker because of its ease in filling and because it is plastic and I will not break like a coffee pot would. (I have broken many).  The streamlined looks is great.'),
(585, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-29', 'Five Stars Love this. Super easy to use and a great price.'),
(586, 8, 1, 4, '2016-09-14', 'Small and coffee not as good as my other one I have a 10 cup Black and Decker coffee maker at my other home and love it.  My coffee tastes great and I actually prefer it over my Chemex.  However, with this one, my coffee doesn\'t taste as good and it\'s the same ground coffee.  It\'s a nice size for what I need and for the price, it\'s a good deal.  I ended up buying a Keurig to have on hand when company comes for when I need more than five cups.'),
(587, 3, 1, 4, '2015-12-09', 'its the best toaster oven I have owned works as designed,  but,  the wording above the start- stop buttons( and the other buttons)  is smearing off. besides that, its the best toaster oven I have owned.'),
(588, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-31', 'Cuisinart 2 slice toaster I love this toaster!  It is very simply made and looks good on my counter.  I am back to eating toast!'),
(589, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-28', 'Mostly Satisfied Received item with glass door detached on one side. Fortunately I was able to re-attach door pin into the frame thus avoiding returning the product. Otherwise it works great. Doesn\'t burn food. The temperature and timers are very accurate. Cooks very nicely. I have owned other Black & Decker ovens and this is by far the best. Price was $25 and was usually around $39 elsewhere.'),
(590, 6, 1, 2, '2016-02-08', 'Loses toasting power This thing has gradually become less and less hot over the course of 6 months. I have to turn it all the way to the highest setting to get it to toast and then sometimes I have to push it down again.'),
(591, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-05', 'Great product for price Love ours and great price! Works great and didn\'t break the bank.'),
(592, 11, 1, 5, '2015-01-20', 'Five Stars gift to my son - works perfectly'),
(593, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-04', 'Waffle time! Works great! The wife loves it. Absolutely no problems!'),
(594, 9, 1, 2, '2016-04-30', 'Coffee doesn\'t heatv up hot enough and you have to add a lot of coffee to get a robust flavor like I prefer Coffee doesn\'t stay hot long. Too many steps to make a cup of coffee. The water container sometimes doesn\'t fit properly. Coffee doesn\'t heatv up hot enough and you have to add a lot of coffee to get a robust flavor like I prefer.'),
(595, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-13', 'So glad I picked this one. Our first Keurig quit working. After buying and trying two others, one was a Keurig and the other was an off brand, I decided to try this. So far, we love it.  I think we finally have a winner.'),
(596, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-26', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker.  Easy to use, no dripping when pouring, and the temperature control is a nice feature.'),
(597, 3, 1, 3, '2015-09-20', 'Okay but not for my needs. I should have purchased a microwave as for my purpose it would have been far more useful. Cheaply made. Was going to return it but decided to keep it 4 the rare occasion that I will use it 4. Had one in my Connecticut home (built in) but I cooked much more then and had dinner parties.  For 1 person and my needs a microwaive is far superior.'),
(598, 8, 1, 4, '2016-04-16', 'Not bad for the price... Great for the price.  Only 2 issues --  brewing does not stop if carafe is removed to pour a cup midway the process and there\'s no automatic turn off of the unit if accidently left on.  So you go through the work day wondering \"OMG did I turn if off?  Is it still on?\"'),
(599, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-03', 'It has survived many moves and still works like a champ This little coffee pot is a tank!  It has survived many moves and still works like a champ. My husband uses this when our Keurig acts up ( which it does often).'),
(600, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Purple Power I love my Kuerigs, and yes I have multiples. I recently damaged one while shipping it overseas, so I bought the K250 2.0. This system is amazing, and provides a vast array of options for brewing. I love that I can go from one mug to a carafe that serves 3-4 mugs of coffee for when I have visitors in my office. The touch screen is simple to use and the instruction manual perfectly explained how to program each step or select different options. Every cup of coffee or tea that I makes comes out just perfect each time. Additionally the color was true to the picture!'),
(601, 12, 1, 4, '2014-09-07', 'Four Stars Works great especially on small counter top space.  The best of two worlds.'),
(602, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Five Stars Great product. Great price.  Fast shipping.'),
(603, 11, 1, 3, '2015-02-06', 'Works fine as toaster or oven Works fine as toaster or oven, but I wouldn\'t have purchased it if I had realized that this model doesn\'t have the flip open bottom that makes cleaning so quick and easy.'),
(604, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-21', 'Great Product Thus far I have no complaints, perfect size good quality !!! Actually a bit bigger then expected. Great for any size apartment.'),
(605, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-12', 'cramped inside but appears fully functional Only had it a few weeks but so far so good! You do need some practice about how long you want your toast dark. Recommended don\'t go past 25-30%. Oh and with the slide out wire grill there really isn\'t much room in there maybe 3 images before your food would touch the top heating element and possibly burning.'),
(606, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-07', 'So convenient This coffee maker is so convenient. I\'m glad I got to read the reviews of this product. Great product for the price.'),
(607, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Best Keurig to date! I love my new Keurig!  They have really gotten it right this time.  It is much quieter than my two previous Keurigs, has a water filtration system (should keep the inner workings cleaner and less scaling deposits), more cup sizes and a nifty little tough screen menu that is easy to navigate.  The coffee tastes as great as ever and there seem to be tons more coffee selections since I bought my last Keurig.  I can even purchase a carafe if I desire!  I only hope that this one lasts longer than the previous ones.  Incidentally, if you provide an unbiased review, you can receive free pods! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(608, 5, 1, 3, '2015-11-22', 'I spent a lot of time researching to find the perfect coffee maker Well it worked for a total of 49 months (roughly $1 per month).........Seems an electronic failure is most likely the reason it no longer functions. I spent a lot of time researching to find the perfect coffee maker. There are others out there that are more expensive and lack some of the unique features that make this one desirable. I especially like the removable reservoir. It is a complete pain to fill a machine at the counter. Also it does not dribble if you pour slow initially and most importantly it makes great coffee. Considering that its competitors would theoretically be prone to similar electronic failure I have decided to buy another one. Perhaps I will have better luck with next one. Also I will have a couple spare parts that may come in handy.'),
(609, 5, 1, 1, '2014-07-26', 'Not a good choice worked for 4 days-was fine no problem, however about a hour ago went into the kitchen and the clock on the coffeemaker was not lite and tried it in several spots, all electric is working fine, but the pot is dead just applied for a refund, sending it back, 4 days working isn\'t a good deal, thought it was great very upset that I have invested in this and now have to go find another coffee pot-will never deal with this supplier on Amazon again'),
(610, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Five Stars It works fine.  No prob;ems.'),
(611, 9, 1, 2, '2016-12-20', '3 STRIKES AND YOU\'RE OUT!!! I have had this coffee maker for 2 years and 4 months and the \"empty/full\" signal doesn\'t work anymore.  Whenever I clean it, which is every day, little black chips come out.  I cannot for the life of me figure out where it is coming from.  I have tried cleaning around the ring of the heating element, under all edges, and still cannot understand where they are coming from.  The problem is that they are in the coffee I am drinking.  I gave it 2 stars because of the programming feature where you set up the time to go on in the morning.  This is my third Coffee-on-Demand, and by far the worst one!  Extremely disappointed and will not be buying another one.'),
(612, 3, 1, 1, '2014-05-26', 'Don\'t buy this toaster oven! Makes toast very slowly. Controls are not intuitive. Unit always emitted a slight buzzing sound when plugged in, even if not turned on. And it broke after 3 years of occasional use (maybe twice per week). No power, intermittent.'),
(613, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-09', 'Great coffee maker for the price Great coffee maker for the price. Love the look and the glass pot is designed for drip less pouring. Good height for us short folks to pour in water. Option for strong brewing really makes a difference. I highly recommend this product.'),
(614, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-21', 'Love how easy it is to clean Love how easy it is to clean...and especially love that I\'m not held hostage to that other coffee maker\'s brand of coffee products!'),
(615, 5, 1, 3, '2014-08-19', 'Cheap Pot But Lousy Coffee This coffee pot was inexpensive, seems well made, arrived quickly and is easy to use.  I like the fact that it easily turns off at two hours and easily turns back on when desired.  There really is only one problem, and that is that it makes lousy coffee. No matter how much coffe I use or how I grind it the coffe is thin and tasteless.  I have used a Krups pot for the past 35 years.  This coffee does not compare, even when I use the very best coffee grounds. Nearly a year later....there has not been a day since I purchased this pot that I have not been sorry..  No matter what coffee I use or how much I use the coffee is thin and weak. If you like strong rich coffee, don\'t buy this pot.'),
(616, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-09', 'Five Stars I like it'),
(617, 6, 1, 1, '2016-08-01', 'If you like your bread over-toasted on one side If you like your bread over-toasted on one side, and just lightly on the other, LOOK NO FURTHER. This one will be returned.'),
(618, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Five Stars Just perfect for one person!'),
(619, 11, 1, 4, '2014-01-29', 'Almost perfect Settled for this one for not being too big nor small. Does what it says and does it well. Pros; Efficient, size is great, heats fast and evenly. Cons: Only one and a real danger is if you manually switch off the timer there is a high chance that it will go into the permanently on state. So users need to be very careful.'),
(620, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-05', 'Works well, careful of \"Stay on\" Works great! Especially for the price. As other reviewers mentioned, be careful about the \"stay on\" setting right next to off.'),
(621, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-10', 'so far so good. We were a little concerned with the seeming ... so far so good.  We were a little concerned with the seeming low clearance between rack and the top heating element, but that has shown to be a problem as of yet.  This unit replaced an older model, the previous version I guess, and this one toasts more quickly and quite evenly.  The previous being the opposite - slow to toast and quite uneven from left to right.  Very satisfied with this unit.'),
(622, 10, 1, 2, '2015-09-17', 'Two Stars I don\'t feel like this works well. You get what you pay for'),
(623, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-19', 'Works Great Great product. We liked the first purchase many years ago so well, we searched for another and found this one. Shipped quickly, and works great. Smaller unit for counter top that does both oven and toaster in one.'),
(624, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-04', 'Five Stars works'),
(625, 11, 1, 3, '2014-09-18', 'Three Stars hard to grill without burning . Timer must be set to very short time'),
(626, 10, 1, 4, '2015-07-22', 'Four Stars Nice little blender, not as powerful as the nutribullet, but great for traveling.  Small and easy to carry.'),
(627, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-30', 'So toasty!!!! :) I bought this toaster oven so I could hear my lunch at work and I was not disappointed. Most toaster ovens only heat the top side of the bread while leaving the bottom warm. This toaster oven heats the whole bread and leaves a slight crisp crunch that is delish! :) I love my toaster oven !!!!'),
(628, 5, 1, 2, '2015-10-10', 'Disappointment The coffee maker worked just fine and we enjoyed delicious cups of coffee every morning for the last 6 months.  However, yesterday, it died on us.  No coffee, and we could not reach the company or the warranty company and are very unhappy. It was a Friday morning when we called both of the above and they said that there phones were out.  What do you think about that?'),
(629, 3, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Recommended but requires some planning. We\'ve only used the oven once but it worked great.  It heated quickly, is easy to use, and cooked evenly.  I almost returned it because the cord is so short that I had to rearrange my kitchen counters to plug it in.  If there isn\'t a plug directly behind, or within 6 inches of the right side of the oven, where you are planning to place it you need should reconsider.  The user manual states that the cord is intentionally short to avoid tripping over it.  Sound reasoning for a kitchen counter appliance.  Overall, I am happy with the purchase so far and it is way better than heating our range up to cook for 2 people.'),
(630, 3, 1, 4, '2016-06-03', 'Well worth the money The oven on our range had quio.  Rather than repair it now, we decided to try using a good toaster oven.  We have found this oven equal to whatever task we asked of it.  We haven\'t toasted anything, but we\'ve baked roasts and pizza,  made cornbread, etc. with no problem.  Someday I may even get around to reading the instructions to see what else it can do!'),
(631, 6, 1, 4, '2014-07-13', 'Good for the price Lightweight toaster, reasonable quality for price.  I\'ve had mine for a couple of months & it toasts unevenly except when I use the bagel setting. My solution is to toast on a lighter setting & turn the toast; slots are a bit narrow & some thick slices will burn on edges.Dial button works well & actually does a pretty good job controlling temperature.  Overally I would buy it again'),
(632, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-17', 'Five Stars Easy to clean and seperate water container that can be removed is nice.  Makes good coffee!'),
(633, 4, 1, 1, '2016-02-13', 'One of the heating elements warped and bent to the point its in contact with the crumb try and its not possible to pull out any This toaster just kicked it in the past month. We have had it for over 2 years and have experienced what others have. One of the heating elements warped and bent to the point its in contact with the crumb try and its not possible to pull out any longer not to mention it probably heats the crumb tray like a skillet then after inspecting this first bent element I noticed the one behind it has a massive glowing split in it. Obviously a fire hazard to the nth degree. Stay away. Worked lovely for 2 years or so but why invite a possible fire hazard?'),
(634, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-03', 'Works well. I bake cookies here. Works well.  I bake cookies here.'),
(635, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-28', 'So far so good The coffeemaker looks nice and does a good job brewing the coffee.  I would recommend to all looking for a good coffeemaker.'),
(636, 4, 1, 2, '2016-02-09', 'Disappointed Doesn\'t live up to the name. While the oven rack is well engineered to fit in the oven at most any desired height, the controls are seriously lacking. Any darkness setting beyond half will burn your toast or treat to a flaming crisp. The toast timer doesn\'t reset if you terminate the toasting before it has rung the bell. Oven times out after an unknown period of time, so if you are cooking low and slow, be sure to constantly monitor, as it will turn off on it\'s own. Once these issues are overcome, the overall performance is acceptable.'),
(637, 12, 1, 3, '2016-09-27', 'Three Stars There is a deep scratch after open the package.'),
(638, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-25', 'Nice, but the toaster\'s kinda slow Beautiful! Fits nicely on my kitchen counter. Sleek design, not bulky. One minor quibble is that the toaster is slow and doesn\'t make the toast crisp. I set the timer to the half-dark bread icon, but it only barely gets brown. I\'ll try the full-black setting and hope the toast doesn\'t get burnt. Still an overall excellent toaster oven for a bargain price.'),
(639, 7, 3, 4, '2015-05-21', 'We finally pitched our Keurig after so many problems with it and looked for something that did the same thing but was not so expensive. Enter the HB FlexBrew. We had recently bought a new drip coffee maker so didn\'t want one that had that included. This model seemed perfect. No, it\'s not as good as a Keurig (when it worked properly) but it does the job. The pods seem to brew a little stronger than the Keurig and the single brew filter needs slightly MORE coffee than you might usually use or it comes out weak. I use the k-cups and the pods that have the soft bottom and both work equally well. I use a tall mug which does not fit in the cup space so I have to use it on the travel cup height which does spit out a bit as the cup is not all the way up to where the water comes out. I have a cat food tin work around :-) A big note is that it only dispenses 10oz which will NOT fill a large travel mug.'),
(640, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-15', 'Fast and easy! Great little toaster, 2nd one. Great price and size.'),
(641, 7, 3, 1, '2016-05-13', 'When setup the coffee maker didn\'t make a hole in the k-cup to allow the water to run over the coffee to make a cup.'),
(642, 7, 3, 1, '2016-07-16', 'It worked great for 6 days. Had a plastic taste at the beginning but that stopped after a few brews. On day 7, I got the blinking light that means not enough water even tho I poured in the correct amount. After reading the reviews, it seems like I\'m not the only one with this same problem. Will be returning it today.'),
(643, 8, 1, 3, '2015-12-20', 'This unit needs to be thoroughly washed multiple times before ... This unit needs to be thoroughly washed multiple times before use. Even then it mat take some time for the smell of plastic to fade away.'),
(644, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-22', 'Works well This works well, once you get used to the settings.  There was an extreme lack of directions included with the oven, so installing the various parts and use of the controls was lacking.....'),
(645, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'Everyone should own ONE!!! I use mine everyday, I love that I am not wasting anything here. Perfect amount for a personal cup, and the service received by Keurig when I called with a small problem, was amazing, so simple, easy and nice employees to talk with. I tell EVERYONE I can to buy one of these #bestinvestmentever');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(646, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-09', 'Love it! Best coffee maker on the market! Love, love, love this coffee maker! I had one that was another brand and it started leaking after about four months of everyday use. I was really bummed as I love the ease of having your coffee without messing with a carafe. When I found my Cuisinart on line I was thrilled! It is so much made than the \"other\" brand.\" There is no comparison. I thought at first it was a bit expensive, but I\'ve bought this brand over the years and knew it was a good product. Well, let me tell you it is worth every cent! It makes your coffee so quickly that the first time I used it I thought I\'d forgotten the water. It also keeps your coffee really hot for your next cup! I wouldn\'t trade it for 10 of the one up  coffer makers! (I have one) This is much faster and your not spending a fortune on pods!.'),
(647, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-02', 'Five Stars Love it, meet my expectation.'),
(648, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-10', 'easy to use oven it\'s really nice to have this at home. it makes the best toast for our morning consumption. easy to use.'),
(649, 8, 1, 4, '2015-10-17', 'I received it pretty fast. Very impressed with Amazon shipping This is a cute coffee maker for a college student. Its small and compact. It works very well. I received it pretty fast. Very impressed with Amazon shipping.'),
(650, 5, 1, 1, '2015-05-30', 'Weak Coffee I bought this coffee maker based on the great reviews that it was the best and looked great.  I am very disappointed and should have gone with something cheaper.  First of all, it is not very attractive on my counter.  It\'s very boxy.  Worse, it makes terrible coffee.  I don\'t think it gets hot enough to decently brew 1 to 4 cups.  I am now stuck with it since returning would have cost me $30.'),
(651, 6, 1, 4, '2015-01-16', 'Good for the price. It does what is supposed to do with some friendly features. It\'s plastic and has a cheap feel, although it looks good. It\'s what I wanted at the price point I was at. Many reviewers have complained that both sides of the toast are not the same and I agree, but it\'s still toast whether is perfectly uniform or not.'),
(652, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Works great. Printing on dials could be slightly larger for ... Toaster oven is a replacement for an old one that died.  It is everything that I need.  Toaster and small oven.  Works great.  Printing on dials could be slightly larger for us old folks!'),
(653, 4, 1, 3, '2015-10-06', 'Ridiculously loud buzzer Ok - it makes toast and does all those other things that you expect from a toaster oven.  It works fine.  The problem is this - when you make your toast, there is not a little \"ding\" or chime that it is done.  No. Instead you have this REALLY ANNOYING, REALLY LOUD BUZZER - THAT COULD WELL SERVE AS THE ALARM TO WAKE YOUR ENTIRE HOUSEHOLD IF THERE WAS A FIRE.  I hate it.  As far as I am concerned, once my kitchen remodel is over - it goes on a shelf and I buy a new toaster.'),
(654, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Pleasantly surprised! I bought this keurig as soon as I saw that they made an ORANGE one!  I actually didn\'t buy it for any special features.  So when I plugged it in, and set it all up and put water in, I was pleased that I could set if I want my coffee stronger.  I was also pleased that I could brew a carafe if I wanted, but the carafe was not included....so that was a bummer.  Apparently there are K-mug type cups out there that will brew 12oz, 14oz, and 16oz cups of coffee?  I do wish that there was a refillable k-pod so I could use my own kind of coffee, I miss that from my old Keurig.  I also wish the carafe was bigger so I could get a bigger pot of coffee.  Over all I really like it and am happy to keep using Keurig.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(655, 5, 1, 4, '2014-11-10', 'Overall satisfied with a few comments....... This device was purchased to replace an old GE that just got tired and decided to stop brewing.  Spent quite a bit of time going over the different coffeemakers and brands here on Amazon.  Finally came down to the Hamilton Beach 46201 and placed the order.  It arrived with the usual \"Prime Time\" speed I have come to enjoy.  The device was well packed and it was quickly unpacked and set up.  One disappointment was that it included no filters and the gold filter I ordered with the device was back-ordered.  It was going to be a few days, so we picked up some paper filters locally.  Cleaned it before use with white vinegar and then rinsed 4 times.  Finally ready for the first pot of coffee and I was not disappointed.  This coffeemaker produces great coffee in a very short amount of time.  It\'s very easy to fill by either removing the reservoir from the back or by filling the reservoir in place from the carafe.  The settings are very easy to understand and it does not require a degree in computer science to set up.  I really like the way I can control the setting of the hot plate for keeping coffee warmed.  My old coffeemaker did not have such a feature and I was always burning coffee. There are a few things I do not care for with this coffeemaker but considering the price I can live with them.  First, it has these strange little \"rollers\" on the bottom which I assume help make it easier to pivot on the counter.  If you want to move it straight toward you it feels like it\'s dragging.  Second, when the carafe is in the coffee maker you can not tell how much coffee is in the pot because the device \"body\" is black and there is no contrast.  I have to pull the carafe out slightly to see what is in it.  Last, the carafe itself.  Perhaps I\'m being too picky, but I do not like the plastic around the entire top of the carafe.  When cleaning, water gets \"caught\" when it is upside down and then flows down when turned upright again.  ( hope this makes sense )  I have yet to come up with a satisfactory way of hand cleaning it.  Even in a dishwasher one would have to be careful about water remaining in the carafe. Well, that about sums it up.  Overall I recommend this coffeemaker with a few \"demerits\".  Those 3 things I mentioned that bother me are so minor I almost did not mention them.  But, I would have wanted to know about them up front when I was looking. Hope this review helps someone.'),
(656, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-04', 'Five Stars love it'),
(657, 5, 1, 4, '2014-03-05', 'Works Well, but... I really like the coffee maker for the most part. The features (e.g., regular and bold brewing options) are great. I particularly like the separate water reservoir that can be detached and filled.  My only complaint is that within 2 weeks of use, while washing the filter basket, it broke.  The part allowing removal of the carafe before brewing completes broke off and won\'t go back on.  A new filter basket can be ordered but it costs more to ship than the item itself.  So, I go without.'),
(658, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-11', 'Bagel setting is horrible!!! The bagel setting burns the outside and does not warm the inside.'),
(659, 6, 1, 2, '2015-05-06', 'Two Stars Only toasted on one side. Returned.'),
(660, 10, 1, 1, '2016-01-08', 'DON\'T DO IT !!!! I just got home to my package. I decided to make a smoothie with 2 scoops of yogurt, 1 cup of water and a scoop of protein powder. The thing started heating up, smoke coming from the side and that burning smell, so no smoothie for me. Bad purchase!!! I want my refund ASAP!!!!'),
(661, 2, 1, 3, '2015-11-21', 'It is okay Really small. The tray is 10 inches by 7 inches. Hard to read the dial settings they are so small. Does the job if you watch it closely.'),
(662, 4, 1, 4, '2016-02-13', 'First Impressions My TOB-40 arrived yesterday.  My first impressions are: From the info page; \"full size interior holds ... and 6 slices of toast\". NO. It\'s a generously sized four slice. The thermostat is pretty accurate. I calibrate temperature devices for a living and I\'m impressed that the oven maintains a temp within 4% (on the low side) of set point. (10 degree average) Better than my full sized oven. The dead band of the thermostat is pretty tight causing the accurate temp and short cycling the heating elements. (Good for not burning things. Bad for longevity. I\'d rather have the former. The warm up time is reasonable. (5 minutes to get close to 250, 10 to get close to 450) The toast timer works well. My morning toast was medium when set on medium. It does not toast evenly like a real toaster. Two heat rods aren\'t enough for the surface area. But my two previous toaster ovens were just as poor in this department. People have mentioned that it gets rather hot. Yeah, but no more than others I\'ve had. The back heats up more than the sides. I\'ll attach a 4\" spacer to the cord keeper to keep anyone from shoving it against the counter back splash. (Probably some bent aluminum bar stock.) All in all it\'s worth the price. A better one can probably be found but the price would be too high for this cheapskate. (Unless it fails just out of warranty.) In which case I\'ll replace it with the $250 Breville. (?sp)'),
(663, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'Five Stars Daughter loved her gift'),
(664, 12, 1, 3, '2016-12-02', 'Three Stars The oven is VERY small.'),
(665, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-20', 'Five Stars Works great.'),
(666, 4, 1, 1, '2015-12-26', 'Cheap and dangerous product especially for a Cuisinat WARNING!!!! SHARP EDGES ! CHEAPLY MADE GARBAGE ! My son sliced his finger open on the top vents  just taking it out of the box. Every edge is razor sharp ! After that whole mess....It\'s too small. It doesn\'t come with a cooking tray and looks very cheap. Looks so different from the photos and videos. Obviously being returned. What a horrible product Cuisinart !!!!!!'),
(667, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-27', 'A great machine I really like this machine very much.  Easy to fill, easy to program, and makes a very nice cup of coffee.  For the money, you can\'t beat it.'),
(668, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-18', 'boring and effective It does exactly what it says it will do. This is the \"hammer\" of coffee makers... boring and effective.'),
(669, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'A Great, Faster Coffee Brewer I love my Keurig K250 2.0 brewer, I have a red one, I\'ve bought about 100 k-cups and Keurig also gave me some for free. I love this brewer because it\'s faster than regular coffee pot machines and that\'s great for when I\'m rushing, and Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(670, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-26', 'But all in all it\'s great. Looks great Does what\'s expected. I bought it to replace a microwave and it\'s taken me a while to figure out the right time and temp to heat stuff up. But all in all it\'s great. Looks great, and does its job.'),
(671, 12, 1, 5, '2015-08-10', 'The perfect size Perfect for my small kitchen counter'),
(672, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-05', 'I love this machine!! Perfect for an on the go person who doesn\'t want to spend a ton on a kurig. I can use my favorite ground coffee or pick one of many k cups.'),
(673, 7, 3, 5, '2016-09-08', 'This was exactly what I wanted and at a great price! Using it at the office, makes a great cup and is easy and works well'),
(674, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Five Stars Great combo unit for one person or small space.'),
(675, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-15', 'Love the pouring feature! This is our second one. We wore out our first, as it was just the perfect design for us. No more dripping or spilling when pouring. We haven\'t received our replacement yet, so am thankful we had the insight to order another before we woke up one morning without our coffee!! I would recommend it to anyone!'),
(676, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-22', 'but heating not quite as even as I would like. On the other hand Delivers as promised for the price, but heating not quite as even as I would like.  On the other hand, didn\'t overpay for it.  Very good at solving basic toasting needs.'),
(677, 2, 1, 3, '2016-02-02', 'Nice Toaster Oven I like this toaster oven a lot, and for the price you can\'t really beat it. However, the timer seems to not work on my unit, and no matter where I set it, the oven just stays on until I manually turn it back to the \"off\" position. So if you are looking for a decent working and looking toaster oven for a cheap price, like me, then this is a good deal. However, you get what you pay for.'),
(678, 6, 1, 3, '2016-02-06', 'I never have any luck with toasters and this one ... I never have any luck with toasters and this one isn\'t any different.  Another reviewer said it only warms the bread - that\'s true unless you turn the dial to the highest setting.  I then press the \"bagel\" button to get my English Muffins toasted. Overall I can\'t complain as the price was right. I just need to get used to this toaster as my last one toasted at a setting of 2, not 7.'),
(679, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-12', 'it\'s been great. I like the look of the coffee maker ... We\'ve had this coffee maker for about six weeks and use it daily. So far, it\'s been great. I like the look of the coffee maker and the fact that there is not a glass carafe. It looks nice sitting out permanently on the counter.'),
(680, 11, 1, 2, '2014-11-03', 'Disappointed Looks good. Not what I was looking for. Plan to give this to someone who will appreciate it.'),
(681, 4, 1, 1, '2015-06-12', 'Well, we\'ve gone over this before. The issue ... Well, we\'ve gone over this before. The issue has been resolved to my satisfaction, thank you. The issue? It came with US-Compliant Electrical Plug, therefore it could not be used at all in Australia. Therefore, it got a 1-stat rating.'),
(682, 12, 1, 5, '2015-03-07', 'Five Stars like it ,,,,works well'),
(683, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-01', 'Great Coffee Maker! Really like the removable water canister and rollers on the bottom of the coffee maker. Easy to use and easy to remove parts for cleaning. Did some research first and this coffee maker got great ratings. Would highly recommend.'),
(684, 5, 1, 1, '2016-01-25', 'Great Features short life. The coffee maker was fine for the most part. I like the feature that allows you to remove and fill the water reservoir at the sink. Longevity is the #1 problem. This unity worked for two years almost to the day. The burner now longer heats and without that, it will not brew. The expect to get more than two years out  of a unit.'),
(685, 8, 1, 4, '2014-12-27', 'Great Spare Coffee Maker Great little coffee maker.  It doesn\'t have an auto off so remember to turn it off.  I bought this in March 14 and is still working just fine in December 14.  I got it for my shop and make about 4 pots of coffee with it a week.  Never had a problem, and is simple to operate.  Fill with water, filter, coffee, and push red button.  The coffee is hot and brew time is average. For my home/personal use I have a fancier model, that allows me to set a brew time so I wake up with fresh brewed coffee to bring to work, but for a small extra coffee pot for use at work you can\'t go wrong with this.'),
(686, 2, 1, 2, '2015-10-29', 'Much smaller than it looks. Doesn\'t shut off when ... Much smaller than it looks. Doesn\'t shut off when door is opened. Rack is too high for broiling evenly.'),
(687, 10, 1, 2, '2015-05-07', 'Doesn\'t blend well and produces a foul, burnt odor I had high hopes for this personal blender, but unfortunately it hasn\'t worked well for me at all. I bought it for the convenience factor, but it has so many design flaws that it\'s not really convenient at all. I would have been better off spending a little more money for a better blender and a separate to-go cup. The blender itself is not very powerful and really hasn\'t been effective for me at all - in the course of making this morning\'s smoothie, I had to stop blending, take off the lid, stir the contents, and add more liquid multiple times. This was for a smoothie made entirely of fresh fruits and vegetables, no ice involved. Also, the blender produces a foul, burnt odor, which makes me worry that I am on the verge of burning out the motor every time I make a smoothie. As for the cup portion, it seems poorly designed and doesn\'t travel well. It is very difficult to clean under the blades, and the lid does not fully disassemble, so it\'s nearly impossible to clean the underside of the lid. There\'s a slot under the lid that I basically have to clean with a q-tip because gunk builds up there, but the lid does not disassemble. Also, the cup is too large for my car\'s standard-sized cupholders. My recommendation is to skip this blender and spend a little more money on a better blender and a separate to-go cup.'),
(688, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-25', 'Unit Caused Electrical Problems and Failed After 2 Months This coffee pot stopped working after 2 months of use. I received this item as a gift puchased through Amazon.com. Prior to the coffee pot failing, the electrical circuit that it was on kept throwing the breaker. We didn\'t associate the arrival of the coffee pot with this problem, until the pot failed and the circuit problem went away. So far the company has failed to honor a warranty replacement despite multiple calls and agreements to do so.'),
(689, 10, 1, 3, '2016-02-29', 'its just ok, I use a protein powder and ... its just ok, I use a protein powder and I usually have to scrap the sides with a spoon half way.. cover is kinda a pain to get on & off and usually makes a mess..... Get the BELLA one instead'),
(690, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-30', 'Very well thought out toaster oven Comparing to number of others I have had this one is very well thought out. Size is just right for everyday use. Spill tray does very important job.  It\'s quite safe from burning your hand when you take toast out. Engineer who designed this oven was a really good specialist. If you are looking for a toaster oven, but not sure about a model, get this one!'),
(691, 8, 1, 5, '2014-12-09', 'Great simple coffeemaker These things are so great that I\'ve got a back-up stash of a couple, in case they are ever discontinued. The coffeemaker is so simple that there is no clock or timer and it does not connect to the internet. All you do is put in the water and coffee and throw the switch. It\'s perfect for making 2-3 mugs at a time without the hassle of loading those stupid k-cups for every cup you want to brew. Plus, since you have complete control over the amount of grounds you put in, you can control the strength of the brew.'),
(692, 6, 1, 1, '2015-11-21', 'Don\'t buy this toaster! This toaster burns the toast on one side and barely toasts it on the other.  Both sides of the toaster produce the same results.  This is one purchase I really regret!!'),
(693, 2, 1, 1, '2015-08-25', 'If I could give this product 0 stars, I ... If I could give this product 0 stars, I would. In 3 instances, I followed directions to toast bread and each time, even at light toasting, the oven generated smoke and at one point, even FLAMES, setting off my smoke alarm and the pleasure of airing out my home for 4 days. I really wish I had heeded the negative reviews about the faulty toasting on this \"toaster\" oven.'),
(694, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-10', 'really like this toaster over, glad i made the purchase. very nice, no issues after using for a couple months.'),
(695, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'good choice really nice looking The carafe slides into the machine so it is very compact I really like this item'),
(696, 7, 3, 5, '2014-05-11', 'Haven\'t had this item long, but love it already'),
(697, 6, 1, 2, '2016-10-25', 'Bought this in May 2015 and am now looking for ... Bought this in May 2015 and am now looking for a replacement in Oct. 2016.  Had to turn dials all the way up to 6 in order to get a slight beige tone!.'),
(698, 5, 1, 3, '2015-02-16', '3 stars It\'s a good coffeemaker, but it failed to meet some of my standards.'),
(699, 6, 1, 2, '2015-05-20', 'Doesn\'t heat evenly after a few weeks. I have to flip the toast on one side. Annoying. After a few weeks of use this didn\'t toast evenly on one side. I have to flip the toast. The tweaks given here never seemed to work sadly and I don\'t want to tinker with stuff that heats up. That\'s what I pay the company to do in the testing phase. It\'s not the best toaster but I am going to use it until it becomes to much of a pain. Wouldn\'t get it again.'),
(700, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-23', 'If you use common sense when mixing smoothies it\'s perfect! I\'ve had this little blender for 2 years now! If you use common sense when mixing smoothies it\'s perfect!'),
(701, 2, 1, 3, '2015-03-11', 'Hmmm, I have mixed feelings about this one I like the fact you can toast 4 slices of bread. But I can not set it and forget it. When toasting, I need to stand close by, otherwise the toast will burn. But its convenient and small for my small kitchen.'),
(702, 4, 1, 2, '2016-09-27', 'Two Stars Looks good! Not too small and not too big , but NO timer !!!.'),
(703, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-24', 'Great coffee maker at a great price. My wife and I love this coffee maker. We both agree it\'s the best we\'ve ever owned.'),
(704, 4, 1, 1, '2015-08-24', 'JUNK, BUY SOMETHING ELSE Junk, heating elements warp and crack and split.'),
(705, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-17', 'Perfect for us We really like this small oven; and ya can\'t beat the price.  Use it primarily for toasting and occasional slow warming.  Simple, old-style (analog) controls; loud bell sounds when cycle is complete.  Easy to empty the crumb tray. The cooking tray could be slightly larger and still fit the oven, which is kinda strange; but since we don\'t use it for cooking, it\'s not a problem. Now, if only it will last 30+ years like the Montgomery Wards oven it replaced... LOL.'),
(706, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-01', 'Five Stars fine'),
(707, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-06', 'Five Stars exactly as advertised'),
(708, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Its great Love it. Heats up really fast. I like having the ability to control the strength of the coffee and to make cups of 4,6,8 or 10 ounces. It is a little big, taking a lot of counter space. I like having the water reservoir so don\'t have to put water in before each cup. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(709, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-20', 'Five Stars Was a gift and they love the oven'),
(710, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-23', 'LOVE LOVE LOVE this blender LOVE LOVE LOVE this blender!  I bought it in 2012 and have been using it all the time!!!  It is October 2015 now, and 3 years later, it is still working great!  I love making my smoothies in the morning in this, and everyone tells me how great my smoothie\'s taste!  It is super easy to use, and I can travel with the top and drink my smoothie on the way to work.  The lid keeps it secure from spills in my car, which is awesome!  It goes through the dishwasher all the time, and haven\'t had any issues.  I love it so much that I want to get another one so I can have extra jars now that my niece lives with me.  She loves making her smoothies in this as well and drinking them on the way to her university or work!  I highly recommend this product.  When I initially bought it, I was skeptical how long it will last since the price was so much cheaper compared to other products in the market, and that is why I waited 3 years to write my review.  It is still going strong, and working as great as it did in day one!  Just make sure you pour your liquids/yogurt first before you put the fruit, etc., and it works like a charm!  LOVE IT!'),
(711, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-07', 'Flexible design for use on a counter top either in the open or under cabinets. This is a great coffeemaker!!  What a brilliant design with the removable water reservoir (like a Keurig) and swing out filter basket.  I don\'t have mine under cabinets but it could be if I wanted it to be.  No more having to lift a full carafe of water over the top of the coffee maker and try to get it all into the coffeemaker reservoir.  Simply take the removable reservoir over the sink and fill it up.  It makes great coffee and keeps it warm (multiple warming levels is a nice feature) with auto shut off if you don\'t finish it or forget to shut it down. Highly recommend it.'),
(712, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-24', 'I highly reccomend this toaster oven. 5 STARS! This is an amazingly good quality product! It makes a more evenly toasted piece of bread. I use it for some over-sized bagels that I like and other toast. The Bagels fit in my 4-slice toaster, but stick out the top and you have to rotate them. Not good. So I bought this oven. We haven\'t got that old toaster out since! One small thing: The entire outside of the oven gets really hot, so be careful. I put 2 coffee cups behind it to keep it away from the cord plug and the wall because the plug might not stand the heat. A right angle plug would be better, but problem solved. I highly reccomend this toaster oven. 5 STARS!'),
(713, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Blending happily It\'s easy to use, handy and a breeze to clean. I would highly recommend this blender.'),
(714, 2, 1, 2, '2016-05-08', 'I do not love this. It isn\'t great for toasting We were looking for a toaster oven to replace our Oster that lasted about 10 years, and chose this based on reviews and cost. I do not love this. It isn\'t great for toasting, it isn\'t really great for heating, and it doesn\'t fit things in pyrex or small baking dishes very well. It has a timer, though, which is why it has two stars instead of one. If you buy this, you will definitely burn one of the first things you put in it. Guaranteed. Tips: -turn down the heat -- do you need something at 350 degrees? Set it for 300 or 275 - set it for way less time than you think -- you can always heat again, but you can\'t unburn whatever you decided to put in there -don\'t let things get too close to the top -- it will get burned in a very interesting stripe down the top'),
(715, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-11', 'Still the best I owned a GE toaster oven years ago when they first came out. It was sort of ground breaking at that time. Black and Decker purchased the rights to the design and now makes virtually the same device. I have tried many other brands, Delonghi, Cuisinart, Hamilton Beach and although they may have had larger capacity, none of the had a combination of quality, ease of use and reproducibility of results. This model has become a tried and true staple appliance in our household and we would not be without it. Don\'t waster your money on the others.'),
(716, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-26', 'perfect! We love it I use it doing pineapple juice for my daughter very frequently, perfect! We love it .'),
(717, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-28', '... I even could not imagine it would be this cool I love it It was so cheap I even could not imagine it would be this cool I love it'),
(718, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-31', 'Does the job - just not for hot liquids Does a good enough job.  I ordered it to blend my coffee, and as it turns out, it shouldn\'t be used for hot liquids.  So I use it for that purpose anyway.  The tumbler can handle it, but the lid sure can\'t.  Anyway, the motor works easily, gets the job done, and it\'s really convenient.  Just get another blender if you want to use it for hot liquids,'),
(719, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Great cheap coffee maker Great cheap coffee maker! Love the timer feature. Grind the coffee beans the night before and coffee is ready for me. Works great. Been using it for a year now with no problems.'),
(720, 12, 1, 2, '2016-11-16', 'Two Stars Not as I expected it\'s really smaller than it\'a shown.'),
(721, 12, 1, 2, '2016-06-05', 'However the new one is much less sturdy and the door to the oven will fall open ... I replaced my old Hamilton Beach with this new one.  they are almost identical.  However the new one is much less sturdy and the door to the oven will fall open without even touching it.  I am very disappointed in the new one as I do not think it is made as sturdy as the old one.  The one feature I do like is that you can cancel the toasting if you want.'),
(722, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-17', 'Easy to program Easy to program, clock is easy to see.  Although there was some mention that it leaked, I  have had no issues.  One must put the reservoir on correctly which is easy to do.'),
(723, 8, 1, 4, '2016-01-28', 'Great coffee maker Perfect little coffee maker. 5 cups is perfect for personal use. Couldn\'t be more happy. Only reason for 4 rather then five is because of how loud it is. You deff will know when its 1 min from done.'),
(724, 9, 1, 1, '2017-01-17', 'Do not buy this item- serves pieces of rubber with your coffee I bought this item on Amazon on 1/26/16 and It worked fairly well for 6 months. Yesterday the system started leaking. Decided to clean the unit. When I drained the water/vinegar after cleaning, little pieces of black rubber came out of the reservoir. Cuisinart  acknowledges the problem but will do nothing about it. My only choice was to take an exact replacement unit which is unacceptable.'),
(725, 5, 1, 2, '2016-11-11', 'Arrived Defective.  We returned it. Poorly made.  The digital clock on the top was not installed correctly and it sits crooked.  The coffee it made was nothing special.  We returned it and wasted our money on a Bella that spills coffee. :-( It seems it\'s hard to find decent quality these days.'),
(726, 11, 1, 1, '2015-07-03', 'It is a nice tour of things that are wrong with toaster ovens. This toaster does most of the bad things found in other toasters, all in one device. Single heating element on top and bottom leads to a ridiculous 5 minute toast time. Thought it was broken. Really thin wire rack feels like you could crumple it in your hands.'),
(727, 6, 1, 4, '2016-04-14', 'Cuisinart equals quality Seems to still be working well.  Only use it for the thick Bay\'s English Muffins'),
(728, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-02', 'Five Stars Doing good so far, complements my all white kitchen and like the squarish shape.'),
(729, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-02', 'Five Stars great appliance'),
(730, 7, 3, 4, '2016-01-19', 'Purchased this machine a week ago to replace a Keurig 2.0 that died. This machine isn\'t as fast as a Keurig but it does make a better cup of coffee. The water gets hotter and pushes through the pod with more force. I haven\'t tried it with ground coffee but probably will when I run out of k-cups. This machine does take a few minutes to heat the water and needs to cool down between cups. I wouldn\'t recommend this for a household of coffee drinkers unless you don\'t mind 2-4 mins to make a cup, and 2 mins between cups. For the two of us this machine is fine.'),
(731, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', '... so it doesn\'t make smoothies but still does an awesome blend doesn\'t puree ice so it doesn\'t make smoothies but still does an awesome blend job'),
(732, 7, 3, 4, '2015-12-06', 'We liked our FlexBrew. It makes a large cup of coffee - their max size is larger that Kurig\'s \'max size\'. But after a few months, the coffee maker took a longer time to make a cup. then it started leaking water on the counter. I discovered that the upper needle that pops a hole in the coffee pod will get clogged with coffee grounds. If you\'re handy with tools you can disassemble the upper part and clean it out. (There\'s no way to clean it without taking it apart.) Take out the 4 Phillips screws, then pop out the two plastic clips that are in the center. Use a flat screw driver to pry the clips apart. Inside you\'ll see a clear rubber tube that you should pull off the nipple. Now take out the two screws, remove the plastic nipple and you\'ll be able to clean out the metal needle.'),
(733, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-26', 'Great toaster oven and a great price Great toaster oven and a great price! I use it every day for toasting, baking and warming up leftovers!'),
(734, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-28', 'I love it! It does the job I love it!  It does the job!  Plain and simple.'),
(735, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-19', 'Nothing but problems with Keurig!! I have had nothing but problems with my Keurig machines. - My previous machine stopped working after less than 2 years, leading me to spend another $90 on this machine. - it doesn\'t work with non keurig pods, so I had to throw 3/4 of my pods away. - I primarily use my machine for hot water- for tea, and to warm bottles at my in-home daycare. When we have company (frequently), the pods are used for coffee.  I was utterly shocked to see that while this advertises 9 brew sizes, your only choices for hot water are 4 or 6 oz...Not enough for a mug of tea, and not enough to warm a bottle- my older, cheaper machine brewed up to 10 oz of hot water. I don\'t understand why you can\'t brew more hot water. I don\'t have time to brew, wait for another preheat cycle, and brew again just to get enough water. So irritated. I have wasted so much of our hard earned money on this company\'s products, only to be disappointed over and over again. I could just cry right now. Which seems overly dramatic, but not everyone has money to just toss away on sub-par products. Of course, I didn\'t realize the issue with the hot water until I had thrown all the packaging away. I was so excited to use my new product, and (stupidly), assumed that since everything seemed to be functioning correctly and it advertised so many brew sizes, it would work great for us. Wrong.'),
(736, 8, 1, 1, '2015-08-26', 'One Star It did not work on arrival.'),
(737, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-29', 'Five Stars This was a great house warming gift.'),
(738, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-23', 'Great as a toaster and mini oven This Toaster Oven is the best one I have owned. It looks nice, is easy to clean, toasts everything well and heats up leftovers quickly.'),
(739, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-04', 'Trusty little toaster I mainly bought this toaster because I trust this brand.  And I\'m happy to say that it\'s the best toaster I\'ve owned so far.  It\'s not entirely perfect as it doesn\'t evenly toast both sides exactly the same, and sometimes it can be hard to figure out the right toasting levels, but this isn\'t a big issue for me.  I\'ve had it for about a year now so I\'ve had plenty of time to perfect the toasting levels and times.  I also like that the bread slots are fairly wide so I can fit large bagels in it and not worry about it getting stuck.  It\'s also a fairly quick toaster.  With other toasters, it feels like I\'m literally pacing back and forth waiting for it to finish.  This one gets hot quick.  And there\'s no annoying ring when it\'s done.  It just simply pops up.  Overall this has been a great buy.  So far, I have no complaints.  I use it often and it\'s always worked great for me.'),
(740, 1, 1, 4, '2016-10-13', 'Easy Setup and Operation Purchased this one as a replacement for and older Keurig that failed finally. Was easy to set up and get brewing the first time. I like the three cup size settings and the options for stronger brewing. I also ordered the My K-Cup Reusable Coffee Filter which allows for using coffee other than K-Cups/Pods. The new touch screen makes for easy brewing. Only negative so far is that it does not have a power off timer like my old brewer, so you have to manually shut it off apparently.'),
(741, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-25', 'Five Stars Good size and very attractive appliance. Very easy to use.'),
(742, 8, 1, 4, '2016-07-16', 'I love this coffee maker I love this coffee maker! It\'s great price. The carafe doesn\'t leak like so many other ones. It gets hot enough, unlike so many other ones. It\'s just the right amount of coffee for a household where only one person drinks coffee.  I just wish it had auto shut off!'),
(743, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Two Thumbs Up! Great toaster.  I\'ve been using this for a couple of years now and no complaints.'),
(744, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-08', 'Not into the Keurig hype! Cheaply made plastic, sent it back. The unit is very large too, took up too much counter space. After reading all the poor reviews, I decided not to fall for the Keurig fad and stuck with the Hamilton Beach brand which I love! Never even used it, just mailed it right back!'),
(745, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-25', 'Five Stars Good quality.'),
(746, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'Best toaster ever Best toaster ever. Bought as a gift for my husband and my whole family is using. Two in one which takes up less space on the counter.'),
(747, 2, 1, 3, '2016-01-07', 'Three Stars Too many knobs. Wish I had gotten a simpler one.'),
(748, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-25', 'bought to replace older model. Works well. Definitely makes pizza, chicken nuggets, fries etc much easier. Don\'t have to fire up the whole oven, or deal with soggy microwave food. Only caveat is I wish it\'d came with 2 racks instead of one.'),
(749, 3, 1, 5, '2014-11-20', 'Easy to operate and cooks evenly Easy to operate and cooks evenly.  Great for singles or small meals.  Stainless steel exterior adds to any kitchen decor\'.  I would recommend to my friends.'),
(750, 12, 1, 1, '2015-11-18', 'One Star did not work, very disappointed'),
(751, 7, 3, 5, '2016-08-07', 'I have had two Keurig\'s and this makes a better cup of coffee, it\'s a little slower but well worth the wait'),
(752, 8, 1, 3, '2016-08-28', 'Three Stars Smaller than I expected. But it was a bargain.'),
(753, 4, 1, 5, '2015-11-25', 'Great little toaster oven Great little toaster oven.  I purchased it for my disabled sister because it seemed so easy to operate.  I like it better than mine.  Almost kept it.'),
(754, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'Perfect for a busy mom I love this machine! I have always been a coffee snob and wanted fresh ground beans every morning so I refused to get this machine. But I learned that I can use reuasable pods and use my own grounds (and save money!) and now I\'m so happy with it. Its easy to set up even with a one year old demanding my undivided attention. Its so easy to wake up, pop in a pod, and press brew when my child wakes me up before dawn. I did get this product for free for testing and I highly recomend it'),
(755, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-19', 'Neat, attractive and makes a good pot We had an older model of a Hamilton maker and it went on the fritz, so I ordered this one based on great reviews. It is, as other reviewers have noted, compact, easy to move and clean, and the temperature and brew strength features are cool. My only demerit comes from lack of intuitive operation. My husband makes coffee for us every morning and is very happy with the HB 46201, but when he went out of town I couldn\'t figure out the programming function the night before and so didn\'t program it. Once I learn to do that I\'ll be very happy with it. I\'m hoping he just stays home, and continues to bring my coffee to me in the morning!'),
(756, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-06', 'Five Stars We are very pleased with the coffeemaker. Like the automatic shutoff. It does make good coffee.'),
(757, 5, 1, 4, '2016-03-21', 'Works great and hasn\'t broken down yet despite rigorous use Works great and hasn\'t broken down yet despite rigorous use. Makes good coffee and my only complaint is that it shows all knids of smudges, fingerprints, etc.'),
(758, 6, 1, 2, '2014-12-06', 'Two Stars Will not take oversized slices of bread.'),
(759, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-26', 'Four Stars No issues so far. Seems to do the trick.'),
(760, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-20', 'Big hype, Big hype, disappointing results'),
(761, 1, 1, 1, '2016-09-09', 'One Star arrived dead . got refund.'),
(762, 6, 1, 1, '2017-01-24', 'This toaster burns everything on level 1 This toaster burns everything on level 1.  It is very cheap and made out mostly out of plastic. I would not purchase this item if I were you.'),
(763, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-06', 'Five Stars i like it it is good for two persons not just one'),
(764, 6, 1, 4, '2015-04-17', 'Very nice toaster and we are enjoying it Very nice toaster and we are enjoying it.  It is a little hard to lift the toast and get it out at the same time or I would have given it a 5 star rating.'),
(765, 1, 1, 1, '2016-08-01', 'Poor quality control We bought this for my mother-in-law who lives in Hawaii. Well she could never get it to work so  it\'s been sitting in a cabinet since Christmas.  Ny husband is visiting right now and looked at it,  and it turns out that the sample K-Cups that came with it were the wrong ones so she\'s never been able to get it to work; that\'s some seriously poor quality control.  How hard is it to put the right kind of cops in the right box?.'),
(766, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'Love this coffee maker This replaces my previous on demand coffee maker by Cuisinart.  Love this coffee maker.  The light coming on when filling cup is a great feature. Recommend for those who love coffee on demand and don\'t want to deal with coffee pots'),
(767, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-04', 'One of my best purchases on Amazon! Been using this for awhile now....love this toaster!'),
(768, 9, 1, 4, '2016-12-03', 'I like this coffee pot I like this coffee pot...  like the looks and just being able to push down the lever to get a cup.  But I agree with other reviews about the cup gage.  Useless - they should either fix it so it works or remove it as a cost effective design.'),
(769, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'and even though it is not perfect, it gets 5 stars because toaster/toaster oven combos ... This is my second one of these, and even though it is not perfect, it gets 5 stars because toaster/toaster oven combos are not easy to find and this one does what it is supposed to do. It is easy to use and to clean and it is small enough to fit on the counter. It just does not fit two slices of toast at one time if you want just toast. No big deal - we use the toaster oven the most anyway. I would highly recommend this item.'),
(770, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-09', 'Five Stars Love it. Dependable, brews a good cup of coffee!'),
(771, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'Five Stars This has been the best one I have had for a very long time.'),
(772, 10, 1, 2, '2015-04-25', 'Two Stars It is not so easy to take away because there is still something below the bottle'),
(773, 12, 1, 3, '2016-11-27', 'Wouldn\'t buy again. Not great.  Bigger and bulkier than I thought it would be:.'),
(774, 4, 1, 2, '2015-12-30', 'Not worth the money Not a fan of this toaster oven.  I miss the timer I had on my previous oven and it\'s smaller then I thought it would be.  Feels cheap and very lightweight and it makes creaking noises when its on.'),
(775, 9, 1, 4, '2015-05-01', 'I\'ve had this coffee machine for a while now and it\'s comment time! First few weeks it was nice. A few times the plunger/plug allowed coffee to leak out. I find it hard to clean the coffee reservoir. Too many corners and groves that are hard to get to. And where the lever for the plunger is seems to have a chamber where liquid can unknowingly be. Condensation after brewing is normal but if you don\'t keep the lids up, funky microbes can start to grow and make coffee taste like yuck! It does keep the coffee hot enough. Would I buy it again? Knowing what I know now I\'d have to say no. I just wonder how long it\'ll take for the plunger thing to malfunction and let coffee leak out all the time.'),
(776, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-28', 'I used fresh grounds to make my brew, coffee wasn\'t hot enough for me drinking black, and worse for my wife who likes it with cream. Didn\'t try the K-cup. Plus there was a film residue on side of cup with more on the bottom. Coffee didn\'t taste very good either. Returned it to store and bought the Bella maker instead, Bella makes a good hot cup of coffee with a lot less residue than the Hamilton Flexbrew. Plus the coffee taste great, good hot cup of fresh brewed black coffee, to me taste the same or better than the high priced places I go to. Save your self a trip to the store, or a ship back, buy the Bella, same price, better coffee.'),
(777, 5, 1, 2, '2016-07-10', 'The front fell off I\'ve had this item less than a month. Seemed okay at first but the hour and minute buttons did not stick out right/would end up caught behind the plastic cover. This was annoying but did not take away from the functionality much.  But today I opened the filter and the entire front cover over the buttons fell off! At first I thought it would just pop back in, but it\'s actually broken. For owning this less than a month, and it not having been dropped or misused in anyway, this is ridiculous!'),
(778, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-07', 'Highly Recommended I bought this for my wife because she always make healthy shakes for us. It is exactly what she is looking for. High quality. Easy to clean.'),
(779, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Great Coffee Maker Works just as described. Coffee tastes great. Easy to operate/program. What more could one ask from an auto drip coffee maker? I would definitely recommend this to a friend.'),
(780, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-19', 'Five Stars I love the settings on this. It works wonderful!'),
(781, 1, 1, 4, '2015-07-01', 'Nice looking machine! Nice system, but splashes too much when brewing.  But I do like the looks.  I have the beige one.  Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(782, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-07', 'Best coffee maker ever! We absolutely love this coffee maker!  We love the reservoir.  We keep it near the sink, so it is easy to fill using the faucet sprayer, but it is also super easy to take the reservoir out and fill it that way.  It never drips onto the hot plate when you take the carafe out halfway through a brew cycle.  Brilliantly designed!'),
(783, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-06', 'kitchen toaster oven Great toaster oven, its a very nice one to have in the kitchen'),
(784, 5, 1, 4, '2016-02-29', 'Excellent coffee. Face plate broke day one. Amazon is replacing it. Love the wheels that help it turn sideways so you can take the water holder off and fill it. Love that I don\'t have to pour water into the top of it like most models. Love that it turns off in 2 hours. Don\'t like that the face plate fell off the first time I pushed the button to open the filter compartment.  Minus one star. Love that Amazon is replacing this unit for free. Coffee tastes great!'),
(785, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-06', 'Nice Convenient Size I bought this to blend my morning & afternoon shakes. It works very well & its fast for adding ice cubes to my shakes. Bought this to replace my old large blender.'),
(786, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-02', 'Died in 20 months. Worked fine for 20 months. Then woke up to NO COFFEE this morning and it acts as though it\'s not plugged in although that is certainly not the case. I unplugged, replugged, checked outlet with other devices, etc. I assume the power supply failed. One would expect such a product to at least last a few years. Amazon customer service was zero help. 30 day time limit BS. :('),
(787, 12, 1, 5, '2014-01-31', 'Perfect for one person This applicance rates a solid 5 stars. For anyone downsizing, living alone, leaving for college, renting a small apartment it takes up a very little space on a counter. Love it. What a great idea for a gift for that college bound person!'),
(788, 5, 1, 4, '2015-07-30', 'Great Brewer at a Great Price Wow!  This is a great brewer, and it doesn\'t break the bank.  Our old longtime coffee brewer finally bit the dust, so I started looking around for a new one.  I wanted to buy a decent brewer, but didn\'t want to break the bank.  Boy, there are a lot of coffee brewers out there.  I read a lot of reviews, and this model got a lot of good ones on several different sites.  About 6 months ago, I purchased a Hamilton Beach slow cooker that got great reviews, so I was hoping their coffee brewer would deliver the same quality.  Bingo!  Right on target.  This is a great little brewer.  I also purchased the reusable gold basket for it.  I like the way you can remove the water container and fill it right under the tap, and the coffee holder pops right open.  So easy. TWO MONTHS LATER:  I just want to add that we\'re still very happy with the coffee maker.  It is really very easy to keep clean and maintain.  I even remember to do a cleaning cycle every 4 - 6 weeks.'),
(789, 2, 1, 4, '2015-04-16', 'Wider than advertised I haven\'t had this toaster oven long enough to comment on its performance, but, relying on the physical description, which gave the width as 14.5 inches, I bought it to put on a counter just that width. The actual product measures 15.5 inches wide and had to be jury-rigged to fit (I was willing to do this because it is practically impossible to find a smaller toaster oven, and the one we had had become increasingly unsatisfactory). I gather that Amazon is aware of the problem (the product page says it is under review because \"customers have told us there may be something wrong with our inventory of the item, the way we are shipping it, or the way it\'s described here\"), but I wanted to make prospective customers aware of the discrepancy.'),
(790, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-01', 'Terrible product support I bought this product in August 2015 and it worked great for 10 months. On May 31, I went to clean the carafe and filter and noticed that the machine wasn\'t on. I hadn\'t lost power or experienced a power surge and, yet, the coffee maker was dark. I called Amazon customer service and while they couldn\'t help, they transferred me to Hamilton Beach support.This company wanted to charge me $12 in shipping AND take 7-10 business days to return a product that I hadn\'t broken! I will not buy another Hamilton Beach product.'),
(791, 6, 1, 4, '2015-01-10', 'WOULD BUY AGAIN IF NEEDED I would have given a rating of 5 stars if this toaster toasted both sides of the bread equally.  However, usually one side gets toasted much more than the other side.  In spite of this, I really like this toaster.  The feature I enjoy the most is the ability to raise the toasted bread to remove it from the toaster.  I don\'t have to reach into the toaster to remove the bread.  Overall, I would recommend the toaster for bread, bagels and even pop tarts!!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(792, 11, 1, 5, '2014-05-07', 'Simple, decent, inexpensive. Seller shipped promptly, and the toaster oven arrived neatly packed and undamaged. I was looking for something simple without too many bells and whistles after I set my super old toaster oven on fire (operator error!) There were reviews about a funky smell. I washed the trays and wiped down the inside good, then turned the oven on low for a few minutes to \"burn off\" any new smells. I didn\'t even notice any smell, so it wasn\'t even an issue. Works exactly like it should and is a perfect size. I use mine to cook small meals, chicken breast, fish, french fries, etc., and to reheat foods. If you are looking for a decent, inexpensive, simple toaster oven, this is it!'),
(793, 6, 1, 4, '2014-02-15', 'Good Looking! It was compact and sleek.  Even thick bread fit in well.  it was  just the basics, but all I needed.'),
(794, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-28', 'I love my new Keurig system Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.  I love my new Keurig system, it works perfectly and brews fast.  Love having the option to make different cup sizes and strength.  I also like the option of being able to buy a carafe, which I plan on doing and will come in handy when we have company.  Love the color also!!'),
(795, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'Pros Outweigh The Cons - a Great Purchase! I love this brewer.  It has a sleek design, and fits in the limited space on my counter.  It was available in red, my favorite color, which was a \"plus\". The reservoir is much larger than my previous Keurig, so it doesn\'t have to be refilled as often.  Service is fast: I\'m walking away with my cup of coffee in record time. The charcoal filter eliminates my need to purchase gallons of bottled water to ensure a great-tasting cup of coffee. There are only a few of negatives associated with this machine:  It will take single-cup K-Cups or K-Pods to make 4 cups in a carafe; however, the carafe must be purchased separately.  Also, it doesn\'t accept all K-cups OR the refillable/reusable pod I was able to use with my previous Keurig.  Guess I\'ll have to purchase the compatible items or watch the YouTube videos instructing how to alter the older K-Cups to work in the 2.0. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(796, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'Awesome. I love this coffeemaker. I have had mine for almost 1 year already and I have zero complaints. Neither the carafe nor the coffemaker drips, even when pulling the pot early, which I only did once to see what happens (don\'t see why people do that actually). Basket R&R is super easy and accessible. The removable resevoir is well designed and has yet to cause me any problems. It can be removed and replaced into the coffemaker with no drips. The unit rotates on the counter on its vertical axis on wheels under the base nicely for setup and filling. One observation though - the coffemaker is 14\" high and your kitchen cupboards are probably 18\" above the counters, and the steam from the coffemaker comes out a small vent in the top center of the unit at fairly high velocity. It is a good idea to pull it out from under the cabinets when in operation (which I do) so condensation doesn\'t wet down the underside of the cabinet. But this is inconsequential to me. Timer and settings are great, nice blue LED readout on the front, looks great on the counter. This costs a little more that some but you will not regret buying this coffeemaker. Oh yeah, guess what ? - it makes great coffee!!'),
(797, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-01', 'Four Stars So far so good!'),
(798, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-22', 'nice easy to use and easy to wash'),
(799, 5, 1, 2, '2016-09-22', 'Don\'t break the carafe! Do not break the carafe! It is hard to find a replacement that fits. My husband broke if after the first use and now I am looking at spending $30 to replace it. Apparently there is no other one that fits than the replacement for this particular model from Hamilton Beach. Now I am stuck with the dilemma of replacing the pot for $30 or just buying a new coffee maker for the same price. Ugh.'),
(800, 9, 1, 4, '2016-12-08', 'Makes good coffee! Who can ask for more Makes good coffee!  Who can ask for more? However, it receives only FOUR Stars due to what I feel is an unnecessarily difficult to remove and replace water reservoir.  I have taken to filling it with it still on the coffee maker. I really appreciate the dispenser.  So much more convenient than a carafe.  I use the gold screen filter as I think it makes better tasting coffee than using paper filters.  Recommended.'),
(801, 12, 1, 4, '2016-11-30', 'Great Space Saver Works great! Toast perfect and the oven is just the right size, wish it had a timer on the oven but other than that I love it.'),
(802, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'A Nice-Sized Toaster Oven I\'m still getting used to this new Toaster Oven.  It has worked very well the few times I\'ve used it.  I like the size too - not too large.'),
(803, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-20', 'Best toaster over for your money I have now owned this product for approximately seven months and have nothing to report but good things. I use this toaster around five times a week from toasting bread to making chicken tenders. It does an excellent job of evenly toasting things and thoroughly cooking others. It heats up quickly and gets the job done, the crumb tray at the bottom even makes clean-up a breeze to handle. Since I bought this product I have not had any issues with it, and it even looks pretty nice on my counter top, the stainless steel being impeccable. It might not be as feature rich as some of those other more expensive toaster ovens, but this one hits the most-bang-for-your-buck category.'),
(804, 7, 3, 4, '2015-01-05', 'We like it!'),
(805, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love my awesome Keurig brewer... I love my keurig coffee brewer...I purchased the orange zest color...I love the touch screen and that it\'s sleek and compact, I also got the thermal carafe for when we have company. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(806, 11, 1, 5, '2014-01-13', 'toaster oven perfect gift I bought this for my mom for Christmas.  I was worried it was smaller than what she wanted, but she has loved it and used it for many purposes.'),
(807, 10, 1, 3, '2015-01-31', 'Small blender with weak blades and chopping power This is a small personal blender. Clean up is easy, doesn\'t take much space, and relatively inexpensive. I wish the blade was more powerful. Don\'t expect too much power from the blend and be patient. If you make the cup too full, it will not blend completely and you have to move the items around or add more liquids to help it blend. This may take several attempts by adding your fruit or vegetable in slowly.'),
(808, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-29', 'Five Stars Love my new coffee maker by Cuisinart!'),
(809, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'Five Stars C'),
(810, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-11', 'One Star does not work properly.'),
(811, 3, 1, 2, '2015-10-06', 'SPILLS ON HEATING ELEMENT, OVEN NOT USABLE ANY LONGER.. :( I bought this oven 14 months ago, and made good use of it during the first 12 months, and tried to maintain it clean. It performed the cooking functions pretty well, no complaints there. However, while cooking a small pizza once, the melted cheese happened to fall right inside the heating element. It turns out, this is the only part of the oven that CANNOT be cleaned. Now, every time I want to use this oven, it smells burnt food with a toxic smell, and I can no longer use it. Not sure what to do with it..!'),
(812, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-04', 'Love my new toaster This really is a beautiful product.  It heats up quickly and makes perfectly even toast.'),
(813, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Keurig Brewing I love my Keurig, the coffee taste good, brews quickly and it is consumer friendly. The Customer Service department provides superior service. It is a pleasant experience to call. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. \"I received compensation/free product for my undisclosed review\".'),
(814, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-29', 'Five Stars Works great!! Great price!!'),
(815, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'Coffeemaker Love this coffee maker because the coffee stays hot!'),
(816, 5, 1, 2, '2015-09-18', 'I am really disappointed as I love Hamilton Beach and our previous one ... This coffee maker worked well for about 6 months and now it leaks really about 2 out of 12 cups of water.  The water seems to be leaking right from the coffee ground filter while going into the pot.  I am really disappointed as I love Hamilton Beach and our previous one lasted over two years.'),
(817, 5, 1, 1, '2015-02-02', 'She says it\'s the best coffee maker she\'s ever had Bought it for Mom for her b-day. She says it\'s the best coffee maker she\'s ever had! Edit: Our 2nd one just fried last night during a power outage. The first one died the same exact way. Pretty lame considering she had a cheapo coffee maker for years that went through several power outages just fine. Needless to say, I will NOT be buying another Hamilton Beach!'),
(818, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-26', 'Glad I purchased it ! Delivered on time and works even better than i had anticipated.  Great Value !'),
(819, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'Five Stars Excelente'),
(820, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Five Stars Just great and the right size.'),
(821, 4, 1, 3, '2016-01-09', 'Heats very well. Could use a light inside and ... Heats very well. Could use a light inside and a timer.  I have to use the microwave timer for baking and broiling.'),
(822, 3, 1, 4, '2016-08-10', '... toasting and limited broiling so far but am very happy with it\'s performance I have only used it for toasting and limited broiling so far but am very happy with it\'s performance.'),
(823, 11, 1, 5, '2016-09-27', 'Love it. Bought this toaster oven for our camper.  We chose this brand because we have an older version that we have had for about 20 years.  It still works great, but we needed another one.  This was the closest we could find to our old one.  We would recommend this toaster.  It is not too big or too small.  A nice size for the countertop.'),
(824, 2, 1, 3, '2016-06-16', 'Don\'t feel comfortable turning it on and walking away Getting the right timing for toast has been hit and miss.  Don\'t feel comfortable turning it on and walking away.'),
(825, 12, 1, 3, '2016-03-16', 'If you like burnt toast get this oven! This toaster is just alright. My mom had the exact same model and it started to burn her toast on the lowest setting. She wanted a replacement but really liked this one before it had problems. I tried to get her to buy a normal toaster and a normal toaster oven but she wanted it all in one. I just wanted her to be happy so I wasn\'t going to fight with her on it. I did some research and I found the same model she had still for sale so I bought her a new one. It came quick enough and was delivered to her house rather than mine which is a great option that Amazon offers for free. She was very excited to get it and try it out so she opened it right away and then started using it throughout the week. I asked her how it was going and she doesn\'t like to complain so she didn\'t say very much. The next time I was at her house I asked her about it again she finally told me that it burns the toast on the lowest setting just like her old one did. She felt awful that I spent the money on it to replace her old toaster oven with the exact same one that has the same problem. She says she just has to remember to pop the toast up before it sits too long so it doesn\'t get burned. What a hassle! So I guess her toast options are \"burnt\", \"more burnt\" or, \"ashes\". The oven compartment works just fine (hence the three starts and not less) and really doesn\'t get used very often but that\'s not Hamilton Beach\'s fault, that is just my mom being set in her way. I used to love Hamilton Beach products. They were my \'go-to\' brand for small kitchen appliances but the last couple of things I have purchased from them have been huge disappointments and really just a waste of money.'),
(826, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-27', 'Satisfied! Good little toaster oven for the $$$.  It\'s perfect for my purposes, but be aware it\'s smaller than the higher priced models.'),
(827, 3, 1, 4, '2016-07-16', 'Four Stars Only thing missing is a lite for the buttons'),
(828, 7, 3, 4, '2014-01-05', 'We use it daily using pods and loose coffee. Works very well.'),
(829, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Five Stars save from cutting on the stove'),
(830, 10, 1, 2, '2015-09-25', 'Two Stars Worked for a few weeks and then cracked and leaked.'),
(831, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-08', 'Five Stars eh, for the price it is what it is.'),
(832, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-22', 'It\'s a great toaster oven It\'s a great toaster oven! Sleek, looks great and performs perfectly. The only reason I have a star missing is because it\'s a bit smaller than I expected. Probably my fault, and it\'s really not that big a deal for me at all.'),
(833, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-06', 'Valued addition to our kitchen. Nice, modern looking appliance that works well. We have used it to make everything from Taco shell chips to pizza to burgers and hot dogs. This unit does all of them well. It took us a little time to learn how to use the various functions available, but no longer than any other electronic item you buy for the first time. Like any other toaster broiler oven, experimenting with various times and temperatures leads to a satisfying experience.'),
(834, 8, 1, 1, '2016-09-25', 'Makes coffee have a plastic/chemical taste I am very disappointed with this coffee maker. After reading such rave reviews I was confident it would make your basic cup of coffee (how hard is that?). But instead there is some sort of chemical film in this product that has made every batch of coffee taste like plastic/chemicals. I\'ve cleaned it thoroughly with steaming hot water and ran hot water through several times. If anything, the chemical taste has gotten worse. I highly, highly recommend investing in a coffee maker that is better quality because it\'s not worth risking putting toxins into your body everyday. I have never written a review in my life, but this product is scary to me and I want people to be warned about what they are putting into their bodies.'),
(835, 4, 1, 5, '2015-08-01', 'definately would recomend excellent product. price was very competitive.delivery service was early , excellent cust service.'),
(836, 7, 3, 5, '2016-08-27', 'I\'ve had this unit for about 2 weeks and it has been very good so far. I\'ve brewed 16oz cups with the Regular and Bold selection and they have worked well. I have not had any problem with exploding K Cups. I use the Walmart brand of K cup and have not tried others. I have not yet tried using ground coffee. Some say the machine is noisy. I have no idea where that comes from. The noise level is very low. Like I said so far so good. Only time will tell.'),
(837, 6, 1, 1, '2014-12-16', '\" This model is just cheap junk. The levers ... \" This model is just cheap junk. The levers are flimsy, and one doesn\'t latch at the bottom at all. \" YES'),
(838, 10, 1, 1, '2016-03-18', 'Waste of money Zero stars. Absolute JUNK!!!! Waste of money. Was placed in the garbage after 1 use. Would not blend anything.'),
(839, 5, 1, 2, '2016-05-19', 'I LOVED this coffee maker SO Frustrating!  I LOVED this coffee maker. The water well is awesome, it slides nicely out from under the cabinet, it\'s attractive and makes good coffee. But after ONE YEAR and 2 months, it died. Now I\'m reading back through reviews and noticing that this is COMMON with this coffee maker. So I guess it\'s built to die after once-daily use for just over a year (or less, according to some reviews). This is so disappointing -- especially when it seemed to be such a nice coffee maker.'),
(840, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-11', 'Four Stars good value and good design.'),
(841, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-03', 'mini pizza toaster My mini pizza can fit inside this toaster. I love using it'),
(842, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-25', 'Four Stars served our need well'),
(843, 1, 1, 3, '2016-02-19', 'Not all it\'s cracked up to be I may be one of the few users to think this coffee brewer makes only passable coffee.  We went from a french press to this because of the ability to make fresh cups one at a time, using different brands of coffee, and because it was so much easier than a french press. I mean my husband was grinding his beans every morning and that was noisy, messy and alot of effort and time, plus stirring the pot midway thru the brew. (By the way, if you decide to have a FP at some point, do yourself a favor and buy an extra glass carafe in case you break the first one.  We always kept a spare on hand so if we broke the first carafe since it is glass, all we had to to do was grab the second one and we were good to go.  Then we immediately ordered another glass carafe to have it on hand in case we broke another carafe! Sounds nuts, I know, but you will thank yourself the first time you break a carafe and can\'t have coffee that morning. And eventually we did break a carafe.)  The coffee the Keurig makes is not as full bodied as the FP and tastes more like coffee you might get at Waffle House.  We use Community Coffee pods which is made for Keurig and this is a full bodied rich coffee but you would never know that using this machine.  So that is the first con.  The next is the high cost of coffee pods no matter what kind of deals you can find versus buying a pound of coffee in a bag.  We bot the Keurig plastic pods so you can use your own coffee to save money but filling those things up defeats the ease of use we bot this pot for.  The next thing is I like to make hot tea but to make a strong enough cup of tea using my favorite English tea I use 3 times as much tea to fill a plastic pod so it becomes expensive and then I still have to make only 6 oz. on strong to get a strong cup of tea so you get even less tea using 3 times as much tea.  The next negative is you have to use bottled water which means you have to buy cases of bottled water which you then have to store somewhere, in our case, the garage and you STILL  have to clean the pot now and then for lime buildup or something that slows the flow down. Like everyone else, we now are finding we have to clean out this \"thing\" that gets clogged with grounds every few cups and you never know when it is going to quit working till you have started a pod brewing.  This is a design flaw you would not think an expensive coffee maker would have.  And lastly and this is a strange thing that I am not sure is Keurig\'s malfunction or not, but for several brews the thing just went nuts and overflowed out of my cup into the spillover below.  Normally 8 oz, was more like 6 oz in the cup but then suddenly one morning it became a full cup and a half. Every time we brewed tea or coffee this happened.  We were on our way to Walmart to buy a new one (we just didn\'t want to give up on this brand and we have two huge boxes of these pods so use up) tonite when I decided to try it one more time and this time it went back to a normal fill.  Have no idea why and no assurance it won\'t overflow again.  But if it does, then we may give our pods to our neighbor and buy something else.  I gave it 3 stars only because it is easy to use when it works and I can make a cup when I am on my way out the door with little fuss even if it isn\'t the best cup of coffee I have ever had.  There are other single cup brewers out there that let you use your own coffee  so we may investigate those even tho they may be more hassle than a pod.  This is an honest assessment of our experience with this maker.  You may not have the issues we have had, but be forewarned.'),
(844, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Perfect Toaster Oven Last one I had that was same brand and same model lasted 5 years of constant use. Perfect size for cooking for 2. My suggestion is using it to reheat pizza and it\'s just like out of the oven! Press bake, set to 400 degrees, press convection, then press start and the pizza is ready in under 5 minutes (watch it) and it taste fresh out of the oven, no more microwave pizza for me!'),
(845, 9, 1, 1, '2015-03-13', 'Coffee pot started leaking after few months when called about ... Coffee pot started leaking after few months when called about replacing it I was told that it is no longer covered under warranty.  I had used same model for 3 years before I purchased this one,  I did not buy it from store so I could not return it.'),
(846, 2, 1, 3, '2015-05-18', 'I thought this was the same size as the old ... I thought this was the same size as the old B&D we had worn out.  It\'s smaller with only a single element in both the top and bottom.  The older model had 2 up and 2 down.  This works, just not as convenient or versatile as the larger one.'),
(847, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Five Stars great product and great price'),
(848, 9, 1, 2, '2016-06-24', 'I really want to love this machine, but no such luck. We awoke this morning to yet another day of coffee all over the counter, in a drawer, in a cabinet and on the floor. It appears there is a flaw in the design that enables coffee to bypass the reservoir entirely and just pour straight from the machine during brewing. We clean the machine after every single use and ensure the components are security fit, but after 5 times of having to spend the morning cleaning a glorious mess, the machine is now in the trash. Cuisinart makes outstanding products, but this one appears to be a stinker!'),
(849, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-18', 'awesome coffee maker This coffee maker is excellent'),
(850, 12, 1, 4, '2016-01-26', 'Four Stars OK'),
(851, 10, 1, 1, '2015-09-29', 'worst blender ive ever bought worst blender ive ever bought. crappy motor- doesnt crush the ice and burning smell because the motor has to work so hard'),
(852, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-20', 'Great Oven. Works like a champ.  No problems in over a year of daily use.  Love this oven.'),
(853, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-19', 'Perfect mini Toaster Oven + Toaster I\'m SUPER happy with this awesome toaster/toaster oven. I chose it in Red because of the price but now I\'m super happy I got it in this color becuase it matches my kitcen stuff. Pros: -This little beauty can be used as a toaster OR as a toaster oven. It\'s easy to switch from one function to the next and the bottons are very easily seen/understood. -The tray comes out easily for cleaning and can hold about 2 slices of pizza etc. - It works great and gets things hot quickly. Cons: -The space for \"baking\" is a little small. This is perect for me, but if you\'re looking for a full-sized toaster oven, this is not for you. Honestly, this little guy is perfect and, though I haven\'t had it for more than a month, it seems like it will hold up well to use. It also sloves the problem of having a toaster AND a toaster oven on the counter which is great!.'),
(854, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-07', 'Fantastic Still not sure about convection part, but oven is fantastic once I figured out all the buttons.  Great Instructions.'),
(855, 5, 1, 2, '2016-12-03', 'Very disappointed. The front plate has broken off two times. We had it replaced the first time and the second one broke within the first month. Now, after 6 months of use, the coffee pot is completely dead! I went to make coffee and it won\'t even turn on! Very disappointed.'),
(856, 7, 3, 1, '2016-03-08', 'Worked well in the beginning. Then started making a half cup. I\'m having a hard time returning it'),
(857, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-12', 'Great Toaster! We\'re loving this new toaster.  It works great for bagels as well as toast, and frozen waffles have turned out better than any toaster I\'ve used.  It doesn\'t take up unnecessary space, too, which makes it perfect for our minuscule amount of counter space.'),
(858, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-09', 'Black & Decker did a real good job in upgrading this toaster oven I just got this a few days ago. I\'m really pumped. We had the old version of this. Black & Decker did a real good job in upgrading this toaster oven. The grill goes in smooth, it is easy to clean the crumbs under as you just remove the bottom tray and clean it. The three buttons are much better than their previous system. You simply have heat at top, mode in the middle, and timing at bottom. And it works great.'),
(859, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-21', 'SMOOTHIES! Prepares my flavorful smoothies in just a matter of minutes! This has become my favorite item in the kitchen now!'),
(860, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'best toaster oven ever made!! This was a gift to my daughter. She loves it and it works great. I highly recommend this product. I have one made by this company & it has lasted over 15 years. It still works great.'),
(861, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'This is the perfect coffee maker for a college student This is the perfect coffee maker for a college student. It is a great size for dorm rooms and I love how I could pick the color to match my room. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(862, 11, 1, 4, '2015-01-23', 'Works really well. No issues so far. Heats ... Works really well. No issues so far. Heats properly and we use it all the time to cook small stuff!'),
(863, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-23', 'greeat little oven Got this to replace old one that oven lever stopped working and its great, works the same as old one with same space inside and the hard to find top toaster and pull out latch on inside oven door (newer models do not seem to have it anymore).'),
(864, 5, 1, 3, '2015-02-01', 'Great coffee maker but it doesn\'t last as long as ... Great coffee maker but it doesn\'t last as long as expected. But while it lasted, it was an easy to use and compact coffee maker producing grate tasting coffee.'),
(865, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-25', 'Best Coffee Maker we have ever owned This unit replaced our original. We had some power blips early one morning and when I went to make my morning coffee I discovered the coffee maker did not work at all. We loved this coffee maker so much because the coffee comes out hot and tasting great. It has a timer feature, a \"keep warm\" temperature adjustment and a removable water reservoir. I bought this unit as a replacement and now have a surge protector in place to protect from power issues.'),
(866, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-24', 'Five Stars Greater'),
(867, 7, 3, 1, '2016-01-06', 'Spits water or coffee everywhere. No window to determine how much water is in container. Must be refilled with water each time you use it.'),
(868, 12, 1, 1, '2015-04-06', 'One Star Too small, \"rickety ansd over-priced'),
(869, 4, 1, 2, '2015-10-18', 'Toast dial is way too sensitive. Two stars because it looks nice enough but the toast function is extremely sensitive. The difference between perfect toast and burned is less than 1/16 inch.'),
(870, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-28', 'Parts keep falling off ... Bought January 2016 ... first month the silver faceplate falls off! I opened the basket and the faceplate drops in it. My husband super glued it back on. Today I  push the button to open the basket and the basket hinge snaps into 3 pieces and slings the basket full of used grounds to the middle of the kitchen floor. Shame ... loved how hot it made the coffee but can\'t use without the basket! Expensive for 6 months use!'),
(871, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-26', 'So far so good. Great quality toaster So far so good. Great quality toaster, really like the digital display and the removable tray is great for cleaning crumbs. Although one potential downside I\'ve seen is that it could be very easy for food to fall in the burners in the bottom.'),
(872, 7, 3, 5, '2015-06-15', 'I\'ve been using it with k cups, works perfect. Haven\'t used normal ground coffee yet but I like the idea of having that option available'),
(873, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-15', 'Five Stars Good deal'),
(874, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-08', 'Five Stars tiny, usefull, perfect'),
(875, 5, 1, 4, '2016-08-03', 'A good coffee maker at a good price A very solid machine, Hamilton Beach makes a good machine at the right price so far I\'m very happy with it. I had other machines that were cheaper then this one and broke apart after a short time. I did have a another Hamilton Beach and gave it away and is still going strong. In this price range this is without a doubt a very good coffee maker.'),
(876, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-05', 'Easy to clean Does what it says it will. Easy to clean.'),
(877, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-24', 'Five Stars Good.'),
(878, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Coffee as easy as 1,2,3 We love our new Keurig 2.0. I had an older model which unfortunately stopped working after moving so many times and being banged around. I was unsure whether or not to shell out the money at this time for a new Keurig but with many summer guests coming to our house, I\'m glad I did. Now they have their choice of coffee in the morning and it is so easy. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(879, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-18', 'I get it that I paid 14 bucks for it but still this is a piece of garbage. This is really s***ty product. The blades are not sharp enough or even rotate mostly. Blade rotation started slipping FIRST TIME I started using it. I get it that I paid 14 bucks for it but still this is a piece of garbage.'),
(880, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-20', 'Just love it! Easy to use Just love it! Easy to use. From bread, bagels, rolls and waffles it\'s been great. love that what you toast doesn\'t fall apart__.'),
(881, 5, 1, 1, '2015-08-25', 'One Star Had two tries and neither worked'),
(882, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-21', 'I have 3 of these; definitely recommend I have 3 of these.  I have one at my house, one at my mom\'s and another one my brother took.  They are great for making smoothies in the morning - just make sure to fill it up with enough liquid (I use water or juice). I like the green color and I got it for $10 around Christmas time. The only other one that caught my eye was the Oster blender w travel sports bottle - prob bc of the look. Definitely recommend!'),
(883, 11, 1, 5, '2015-05-06', 'Five Stars Works perfect'),
(884, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-17', 'Good value. Good value.'),
(885, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-18', 'I love it because I don\'t drink much coffee and one cup at a time is easy and it\'s not wasteful'),
(886, 6, 1, 2, '2016-01-20', 'I like the clean look of the toaster and it worked ... I like the clean look of the toaster and it worked fine at first. But only after using it for few month, my bread and bagels are coming up all burnt. Settings are from one to six, it was fine to toast the bread at setting number 3 at first but now it burns even at setting number 2.'),
(887, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Five Stars great toaster!'),
(888, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-05', 'Love it! Perfect for my small place.'),
(889, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-05', 'Five Stars Works great.'),
(890, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-06', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker, my second one. Makes great coffee and is super easy to clean.'),
(891, 3, 1, 2, '2015-10-08', 'Its okay. This is okay.  Once it heats up its fine, unfortunately this is one of the slowest heating up toaster ovens I\'ve ever had.  Also, the stainless steel finish is coming off.'),
(892, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-05', 'Super convenient, great variety of coffee Super convenient, great variety of coffee...coffee comes out hot...i had a single serve brewer which had a screen for your coffee and it always made a mess in the sink rinsing it out..coffee never came out hot either...my new keurig is wonderful!'),
(893, 5, 1, 1, '2014-05-12', 'Great coffee maker Ok so I\'ve had this coffee maker for barely a year and its dead now...used it one a day was very easy on it and the thing is dead what a POS ...never again will I buy a product from this company... If you plan on buying this this good luck I\'m really liking this coffee maker...I love how I can lift off the water container in the back and fill it with water it saves any water spilling onto my counter...the light display in the front looks really nice and the Crome finish on it looks very nice in my kitchen ....worth every dollar'),
(894, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-28', 'very prteyy and clean lines My grandparents love this!  They also thought I had special pull with Amazon as I ordered the item on sat and they received it on Monday!  Price is so competitive. ..even with my macy\'s coupon it was still a few bucks less.'),
(895, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-30', 'Good toaster oven, small footprint, good results Good toaster, used mainly for small pizzas, nachos, and to re-warm food.  Overall it has performed as expected and its small footprint is nice.'),
(896, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-10', 'Five Stars great coffee maker!'),
(897, 7, 3, 5, '2015-12-07', 'great'),
(898, 11, 1, 3, '2014-10-10', 'Small Cooking Surface. Read the Discription closely! Works as advertised. Very Small cooking surface.  Used in a vacation cabin, Fine for a couple who don\'t cook! Read the description closely before you buy!'),
(899, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-12', 'Five Stars very good for its price'),
(900, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-22', 'Used it 5 five times and it burned up.  Smoke coming out of it. I\'ve used it maybe five times since I bought it\'s dead now.  It literally burned and was smoking.  All I blended was some frozen fruit and milk.  Be warned.'),
(901, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-25', 'Five Stars Quality product.'),
(902, 5, 1, 4, '2015-11-27', 'nice works well , nice features'),
(903, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Perfect brewer for entire family I love that you can brew 1 cup at a time. This machine is perfect for the whole entire family to have freshly brewed coffee or hot coco at the time they wish.'),
(904, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-15', 'Overall all a good product! I have had this coffee pot for a couple of months, works well. The light over the cup is very nice and the clear container for water a great idea. Along with the usual settings you can set the time to turn off after brewing - a nice feature for coffee that tends to get bitter the longer it stays on. I don\'t see the need for the filters for the water, looking closely the water can flow under the filter so I use filtered water instead. The only negative so far, the water bin takes a long time to completely dry in this climate with typically higher humidity. Overall this is a good product.'),
(905, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-28', 'Excellent .. Does an excellent job, and it really is big enough for a 2\" pizza.  I was skeptical but am happy to admit my skepticism was unjustified.  And with the convection function turned on, it cooks SO quickly and efficiently.  I couldn\'t be happier with this oven.'),
(906, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', 'Perfect fit Love this coffeemaker!  All I wanted was a small coffeemaker, that makes good coffee.  I get 2 and a half large mugs of coffee which meets my needs. The coffee stays warm for hours and still tastes good. It\'s light weight and fits under my cabinets ( which a 10 cup coffee maker won\'t fit because the cabinets where hung too low, not enough space between the cabinet and the counter ) it doesn\'t have a clock but don\'t need one because microwave and oven have clocks. I don\'t need all the bells and whistles fancier coffee makers offer.  Easy to clean. Good price.'),
(907, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Love the carafe option! We love the versatility of the carafe option!  This brewer is sleek and can fit small spaces- exactly what we were looking for!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(908, 3, 1, 3, '2014-03-30', 'Cheaply made in some respects This oven works okay, but it does get mighty hot on the outside so be careful.  There is really no excuse for the lack of insulation of some sort to protect people from an ultra hot surface, and it\'s just plain dangerous if anything is close enough to melt or start on fire.  The buttons feel cheap too.  Overall, this is a $30 oven at best.  Try Hamilton Beach.  I had one that worked really well but had to give it up because of the size.'),
(909, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-26', 'Best coffee maker I\'ve ever owned! I have owned this coffee maker for almost 2 years, and it\'s been the best one I\'ve ever had.  My problem with most coffee makers is that the coffee is not hot enough, and who wants to drink luke warm coffee?  This one has continued to brew good, hot coffee, every day (sometimes twice a day). I would definitely recommend.'),
(910, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-28', 'Features really work Well engineered. Nice features that really work'),
(911, 11, 1, 4, '2015-02-01', 'Good value The second compact toaster oven I bought in the last year.  The first was a piece of junk and bearing in mind that I have zero food preparation skill this does the job.'),
(912, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'I am glad that I purchased it Attractive design and very well built.  I have used this for a few months now and cannot find a fault.  I am glad that I purchased it.'),
(913, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-03', 'One Star this thing doesn\'t mix at all....'),
(914, 5, 1, 2, '2016-10-12', 'Two Stars Unfortunately arrived with the bezel already broken.'),
(915, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-28', 'Definitely recommend!! Love this machine! The design is really neat. Makes a great cup of coffee. Definitely recommend this. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(916, 12, 1, 4, '2016-12-28', 'but it\'s been working great. There\'s only one slot for the toaster though ... I bought this as a gift but the recipient decided they didn\'t want it; so I\'ve been using it myself instead of a regular toaster. It\'s SMALL, much smaller than a regular toaster over, but it\'s been working great. There\'s only one slot for the toaster though it holds two pieces of bread at the same time. I haven\'t used the oven portion yet, as it\'s only big enough for small items, but I think it\'ll work well enough for chicken nuggets or other smaller meals.'),
(917, 3, 1, 5, '2014-09-16', 'Sleek! Great oven!  Fits a medium size pizza.  Very nice looking too!'),
(918, 6, 1, 1, '2014-09-06', 'This toaster emits a burning plastic odor. Cuisinart calls it the toaster\'s \"new car smell\". That\'s not safe or healthy! The Cuisinart CPT-142 toaster emitted a noxious burning-plastic odor. When I called Cuisinart to request a return, the representative told me that the burning plastic is the toaster\'s \"new car smell\". They said that some toasters of this model emit the burning plastic and some don\'t, but they sell both kinds under the same model number and you never know which one you\'ll get. I asked them to replace mine with one that doesn\'t emit the burning plastic. Although they eventually agreed, they charged me for the shipping!'),
(919, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-16', 'Works great! I love that there is no carafe Works great! I love that there is no carafe. Nothing to break and replace. It\'s easy to use and I love the 1-4 cup feature that keeps it extra hot.'),
(920, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-12', 'Five Stars great toaster'),
(921, 2, 1, 2, '2016-04-11', 'Metal on the top is sharp and cut my finger open. This works fairly well, but I just sliced open my finger on the metal on the top of the unit. Very sharp and dangerous! I have had it for a month or so, so now I will need to decide what to do with it, since I can\'t risk my kids cutting themselves. Very frustrating since I chose this item for its high ratings.'),
(922, 3, 1, 5, '2015-04-02', 'Five Stars love it, can make just about anything in this oven'),
(923, 5, 1, 3, '2015-07-06', 'it works fine. Caraffe spills while pouring when it is full. Display is very large and bright, no option to dim. Otherwise, it works fine.'),
(924, 12, 1, 5, '2016-11-26', 'Five Stars Great addition to my kitchen.'),
(925, 6, 1, 5, '2016-09-13', 'new taoster meets expectations.'),
(926, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-10', 'Love love love my Keurig! I love my Keurig- it\'s one of the best purchases I\'ve ever made. My boyfriend and I save a ton of money by using K Cups instead of buying coffee out at coffee shops or brewing with some crappy brewer. It\'s an investment, yes, but it\'s beyond worth it.'),
(927, 6, 1, 3, '2015-12-05', 'Button Descriptions Washed Off My cleaning woman uses Lysol All-Purpose Cleaner to clean my kitchen, and there has never been a problem with this for years. Until I bought the Cuisinart CPT-142 Toaster, that is. The words bagel, defrost, reheat, and cancel, as well as the name, Cuisinart, which are printed on the front of the toaster dissolved into tiny pieces when washed. All that is left are partial words and flecks of paint (?) stuck to the toaster. Mind you, she lightly sprays a cloth and wipes the appliances down. Come on Cuisinart. You couldnt make a toaster that could withstand a popular kitchen cleaning product. I expect more than substandard products from Cuisinart.'),
(928, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Nice stainless accents and perfect when left out on the ... I was looking for a counter friendly space saving toaster oven that I could use for toast or to warm up some left overs, this fits the bill perfectly! It\'s not a substitute for a full oven but ideal for toast and heating up left over pizza. Nice stainless accents and perfect when left out on the counter. Highly recommended!'),
(929, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'This is a great coffee pot This is a great coffee pot. Easy dispensing into your cup with a light tom view as it fills.Delivers really hot coffee and stays hot for later cups. The water tank seems a bit flimsy but so far works just fine.'),
(930, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-07', 'Toaster oven great addition This toaster was replacing a regular toaster so I could  have more counter space. The oven lets my 5 kids heat up various foods. Holds upto 6 halves of  mini hogie rolls, or 4 reg sized bagels. I worried it would take long to toast-not at all! And if I use broil setting-just one side toasts(think bagels). Very happy with this.'),
(931, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Easy to make coffee and the detachable water cantainer makes ... well made and a  pleasure to own.Easy to make coffee and the detachable water cantainer makes it a breeze to fill with water.'),
(932, 7, 3, 5, '2014-08-17', 'Coffee maker Hamilton Beach Flex Brew'),
(933, 5, 1, 4, '2017-01-17', 'Really like it except for one problem. After years of Cuisinart coffee makers that didn\'t last, I decided to try this one.  Mostly a good decision.  It makes excellent coffee.  I use the Bold option which I think takes a little longer to brew but also needs a bit less coffee. I like that it sort of rolls on my counter, making it so easy to move around.  Filling the water reservoir is easy, even one handed, as is the coffee basket.  My only complaint is that the face plate over the controls, came off the very first time I pushed the button for the coffee basket to turn out and does so almost every time.  It\'s easy to push back on but really Hamilton Beach, that shouldn\'t happen.  That\'s why this is 4-star instead of 5.'),
(934, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-14', 'Five Stars Best kitchen product! Countertop friendly too'),
(935, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-28', 'This item works great!!!! Simple to use and Kcups fit great!'),
(936, 10, 1, 3, '2015-11-20', 'Has a funny burning smell when you have it running for more ... Has a funny burning smell when you have it running for more than 15 seconds and it doesn\'t like to bend up anything frozen. But it works well for when I want a smoothie for breakfast'),
(937, 2, 1, 3, '2016-09-02', 'but disappointed in toaster Haven\'t used oven yet, but disappointed in toaster.  Very had to regulate.  Either too light, or burned.  Also, it seems to dry out the bread.'),
(938, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-14', 'Great Coffee Finally found a great coffee maker without spending a fortune.'),
(939, 2, 1, 3, '2016-04-25', 'Three Stars It is ok!'),
(940, 8, 1, 1, '2015-12-14', 'BAD SWITCH DON\'T BUY IT Bought this coffee maker in August and here it is December 14th and it quit working already.'),
(941, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'Great coffee maker. Great price Great coffee maker. Really like the removable reservoir and the swivel feature makes it that much easier.'),
(942, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-18', 'and this is one of the best yet. We love the LED light feature that ... We\'ve used decanter-type coffee makers for years, and this is one of the best yet. We love the LED light feature that turns on and lets you actually see the coffee level in the cup.  The notification beeps are kind of quiet, but that is not much of an issue for me.  As long as there is coffee ready when I show up with my mug, I wouldn\'t care if the machine whistled Dixie.  The carbon packs are a nice feature, and since we use only filtered, purified water, our coffee tastes wonderful every time.  We recommend using paper filters and keeping the machine very clean to prevent some of the leaking problems mentioned in other reviews.  This is the third machine of this type we\'ve purchased over the last 30 years, and we\'ve never had leaking problems caused by poor maintenance.'),
(943, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-23', 'Five Stars Small good for college students.'),
(944, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-18', 'Great coffee pot. Really a well built unit.  Just received it and made my first pot of coffee.  Love the light, it makes it so much easier to see the cup is full.  Easy to use and the coffee tastes great. It is replacing my old Hamilton Beach Brew Station, which I always loved.  Just recently it started leaking out the bottom, however after reading negative reports on the replacement I decided I had better look elsewhere for a replacement.  I am very pleased with the Cuisinart DCC-3000.  So easy to fill with water.  I did find the coffee was weaker with the same amount of water and the same amount of coffee then what it was with my old Hamilton Beach.  I will try it tomorrow with the paper filter and see if that makes a difference.  Great service from Amazon also.  Life is Good!'),
(945, 12, 1, 3, '2017-01-11', 'Not suitable for toasting anything but small bread and bagels. It does what it claims to do. But the toaster part is lacking. Because it\'s over the oven, there isn\'t much room for the bread shelf to drop. If you use full size bread the top doesn\'t go down into the toaster.  Turning the bread sideways works, if you do one slice at a time. But it\'s not long enough for two slices turned sideways. I realize there are some breads that would fit.  But not any that I buy. And this limitation on bread size as a serious drawback.'),
(946, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-03', 'Great Value for the money & makes a delicious pot of coffee! I\'ve spent far more money on other coffeemakers that in a short time have had multitudes of leaks and/or problems. This coffee pot is easy to use, easy to fill, easy to clean and my husband swears it makes the best pot of coffee he\'s had in years. I was reluctant to get a glass vs stainless carafe for fear of the \"burnt coffee\" taste that often results, but that doesn\'t happen with this Hamilton Beach, perhaps due to the heat setting options? We love it!'),
(947, 2, 1, 1, '2016-08-03', 'Cheap product Took a week not to have burning smell I needed it so I did not send back.'),
(948, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'Five Stars Very easy to use.  Love it.'),
(949, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'LOVE, LOVE, LOVE MY COFFEE MAKER!! It is so cool and easy to operate. It has three temperature levels (I use the lowest for brewing iced tea)--it is easy as pie to program and if I want my coffee to stay warm after the two hour shut off, I just turn the power button off then on again! Buys me two more hours of hot coffee! You can also use the smaller filters too! A definite YES if you\'re toddling on the fence.'),
(950, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'Excellent Coffee Maker and Priced Right!! I purchased the Hamilton Beach 46201 coffee maker about 2 weeks ago. So far, I am extremely pleased with it. Being able to remove the water reservoir to fill it (as opposed to only pouring water into it) is a nice feature. The temperature (plenty hot) and flavor of the coffee have both been great. The unit itself is quite attractive, so it certainly isn\'t an eye sore like many coffee makers are. I would highly recommend this to anyone looking for a new coffee maker. (We did have an oops here and smashed the carafe by accident on the garage floor. I did find a replacement carafe after searching around on the internet for a bit. I wish Amazon had the exact matching carafe for this unit. If they do, I apologize, but I couldn\'t find the one identical to the one we broke for sale on Amazon.) --roughly 2 months since purchasing this coffee maker, and still very pleased. It works great all of the time. I wish we had purchased this one a long time ago so we didn\'t have to battle with some of the other coffee makers we\'ve had. A+++'),
(951, 11, 1, 4, '2014-10-16', 'Nice Oven for Toast and Reheats There\'s really nothing wrong with this Toaster Oven except the top dial where you set the time or switch it to on mode (where you have to remember to turn it off)...my wife had to get used to that. The real reason I gave it only 4 stars is that my last B&D toaster oven came with a little metal tray with a front handle that was real handy for heating up pizza slices or heating up rolls and many other things. This one comes with the grate and just a little tray that fits underneath the grate to catch any drips...but it\'s not even close to being as big as the grate itself. I measured the inside of the oven and found a little set here at Amazon that included a tray and a little broiling pan that fit nicely inside on top of the grate. Why B&D left out such an obvious accessory I will never know.'),
(952, 6, 1, 3, '2015-07-20', 'Good exterior design but mediocre performance PRO: (1) it\'s indeed compact (2) very nice exterior design (3) easy to clean. CON: (1) does not toast both sides evenly (2) too small for larger than sandwich-size bread (3) no bell to alert you when it\'s done (4) does not toast dark, even at highest setting (5) does not push toast up high enough when the handle is raised--need to fish it out with a knife sometimes (NOT recommended with the toaster plugged in). Would not recommend except for tiny apartments,.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(953, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-05', 'This thing was my least favorite purchase of the last year This thing was my least favorite purchase of the last year. It\'s dangerous to use, the back gets crazy hot and heats up the cord if its too close.The thing offgassed a very freaky chemical smell for a whole week after getting it. Also, its confusing to figure out what all the knobs do. The timer continues even after the machine is unplugged, which I make a point to do because im pretty certain this is a major fire hazard. Dont recommend this product, but honestly it came so wrapped up with all the little pieces I was too lazy to return it... They got me!.'),
(954, 4, 1, 5, '2016-04-12', 'Five Stars This by far the best toaster oven I have ever had. Easy to clean and it\'s perfect'),
(955, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-27', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(956, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-03', 'Five Stars This is exactly what I was looking for.'),
(957, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-31', 'Five Stars No complaints.'),
(958, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-15', 'Both work great. Second one I purchased.  Both work great.'),
(959, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-04', 'Quick brewing Quick brewing time, auto-programming, easy to operate and brews with no mess'),
(960, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Great transaction.Great seller, Great product!!! Shipment was quick ; product is awesome everything stated and more! Excellent transaction ! One option I didn\'t even realize the coffee machine had; is it lights up the cup/mug as your filling your cup or mug awesome feature ....!!.,'),
(961, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-06', 'Great coffee maker We have two of these.  One for our home, the other for our RV.  Great coffee maker.'),
(962, 3, 1, 4, '2015-06-30', 'Black and Decker toaster oven Oven is larger than the old one it replaced. There is not enough room on my counter for both my microwave and the toaster oven. The oven sits on my dishwasher next to the counter. I was very disappointed the cord is only about 1 foot. I had to buy a heavy duty 3 foot extension cord in order to use it. The instruction booklet says most of the presettings are at 400 degrees and shows how long it preset is. eep the booklet handy and read it. It does go to 450 manually. Potato preset cooks at 400 for 45 minutes. Baked potatoes came out perfect. Toast setting also works well but I need to raise the rack because the toast was too burnt on one side. I cooked pepperoni pizza rolls at 425 for 20 minutes. They were great. I am very satisfied with the performance. I like that the display shows the temperature as it preheats. When using the presets, the display shows the temperature and time remaining. The alarm when cooking ends could be a little louder.'),
(963, 8, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'Five Stars Love this little coffee maker it is perfect for two or three people and does the job very efficiently!'),
(964, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-16', 'Fire Hazard! Same problem with faulty heating element!'),
(965, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-22', 'Don\'t buy! Piece of garbage the heating element went out after3 1/2 months of light usage'),
(966, 9, 1, 4, '2016-04-23', 'This coffee maker is great. I love that you can program the coffee ... This coffee maker is great. I love that you can program the coffee maker the night before and wake up to the coffee already made. The only draw back is that the cup area isn\'t tall enough for most go cups I have. I love this coffee maker.'),
(967, 4, 1, 4, '2016-06-21', 'Four Stars It does make some noise when toasting.'),
(968, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-23', 'Five Stars Convenient to fill'),
(969, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-12', 'Must have for any kitchen. These are a must have in any kitchen.  I love toaster ovens and this B&D one is one of if not the best one I\'ve ever used.  So practical that I find myself using it more and more each day.'),
(970, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-14', 'This toaster oven was a great investment. I bought it for my Mom and ... This toaster oven was a great investment. I bought it for my Mom and her Caregiver, and they say it works well. It is very convenient for cooking smaller food items, reheating and toasting.'),
(971, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'Five Stars Slick awesome design, proven company.'),
(972, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-08', 'Very good! A good, simple, clean design and a powerful motor makes this the darling of my kitchen. We use this a lot, for smoothies, veg, drink, and even some sauces.'),
(973, 8, 1, 5, '2015-03-10', 'Five Stars works greatAAAAAAAAA+++++++++++'),
(974, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-31', 'Very Nice coffee maker Very Nice coffee maker, I like how the water decanter comes off the base and the coffee filter pops open in the front. Even received a day ahead of schedule.'),
(975, 7, 3, 5, '2016-10-28', 'All I wanted is one cup of coffee to get me going in the morning and this was perfect. Using K-cup or your own brew works great. The only con, which is really no big thing, when using regular ground coffee, it leaves a some grounds in your cup. I like my coffee a bit strong, so I prefer the grounds method. Plus K-cup\'s can get a little expensive. FYI...Black is in-store, red,order online.'),
(976, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-26', 'We like it. Follow directions We like it.  Follow directions!!  While toasting, it seeps steam from the bread\'s moisture out and looks like smoke, but it\'s not.'),
(977, 12, 1, 5, '2014-05-05', 'LOVE this little thing!!! I seriously can\'t rave enough about this item.  Years ago, when we switched over to a toaster oven, we all hated it.  We replaced several of them because we could NEVER get them to TOAST a piece of bread correctly.  I\'ve been looking for a unit like this forever and when I found it on here, was absolutely thrilled.  This item will not disappoint.  Its sleek, fits nicely on my small countertop, actually TOASTS my bread, and for the few times that I actually use the toaster oven works very well.  Everyone in my house is very happy to have a toaster back and the addition of the built in toaster oven, compliments both worlds.  For once I didn\'t get burned on a purchase (pun intended).  Buy this.  You\'ll love it and you just can\'t beat the price.'),
(978, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-20', 'Excellent decanter I love that the decanter does not spill. I\'ve had that problem with all my coffee machines in the past. No more having to wipe the counter and/or the floor after pouring myself some coffee!'),
(979, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-29', 'Love this is the 2nd time we bought this Cuisinart..Love it.'),
(980, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-26', 'Love the white color Love the white color, very modern looking. It gave us a little trouble at first but it works well now.'),
(981, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-28', 'Five Stars Excellent quality. Easy to fill and operate.'),
(982, 1, 1, 1, '2016-06-28', 'None of my K cups that I currently have will ... None of my K cups that I currently have will work.  Even using the plastic unit to brew your own coffee gives me the message that the K cup is incompatible.  I previously had Cuisinart brand for 5 years that finally gave out.  I understand there may be away to block the sensor but if that does not work I will get rid of it and purchase another brand.'),
(983, 6, 1, 4, '2014-01-31', 'Good product A good toaster is a good toaster.  Only issue for me is the cord is short so flexibility to put on a counter--depending on location of outlet --is limited. Nice, clean appearance and toasts well.'),
(984, 9, 1, 3, '2016-08-08', 'More good than bad, but it doesn\'t shine. Lasted about a year, two or three pots a day, with regular cleaning. Then it started leaking and wouldn\'t stop.  For the price, that\'s really not a bad run.  It survived through about 1000 pots of coffee. I wouldn\'t buy another one, but I don\'t regret having bought the first one.  It did make decent joe.  Keeping it clean was a chore, and hot water running through it did tend to warp the lid.  I used the timed brew function regularly, and it never failed me. I\'ve got no idea whether or not the built in water filter actually does anything.  As far as I can tell, there\'s no reason to think that the water really flows through the replaceable filters, they just sit sort of near the reservoir outflow.  If the filer is a big part of your buying decision, You may want to consider other options.'),
(985, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'One of the best toaster ovens I have purchased One of the best toaster ovens I have purchased, does not dry out your toast like the last one I had. Easy to clean.'),
(986, 2, 1, 1, '2015-03-05', 'To toast you have to turn the knob past 10 ... To toast you have to turn the knob past 10 minutes and then back to the desired time.  The knob was extremely hard to turn back, really hurt my wrist.  Returned the unit as defective.'),
(987, 7, 3, 5, '2014-03-01', 'ok everyone, I read all the bad reviews about this and decided to get it anyway. Well, I am very happy with it. I have had no leaks except when I forgot to push down the lever that said always push down. it tells you to pour water slow and you should do this. I learned by using it how much water I want to make it stronger. I have also used big cups where I brew two cups in a row. I love this!!!!!!!!'),
(988, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-11', 'DELIGHTED with this machine DELIGHTED with this machine! Was tired of the weak coffee my old machine made.  Although this one is a bit loud, it makes great coffee.  Great feature is the removable water tank from the bank (easy to fill, easy to clean when needed). The pot also smoothly pulls out. The side opening coffee filer is much handier - my old one lifted up, tall - so that it had to be pulled out even farther.  And I like the buttons on the top of the machine; on my old machine the buttons were on the bottom and on occasion they\'d get hit and the machine would turn on.  Only thing I would change is change the glass carafe to a thermal pot; I turn the heat off soon after I pour so the coffee doesn\'t sit on the burner for long.  Really happen with this coffee maker!'),
(989, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-04', 'love it just what I wanted and expected, love it'),
(990, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-17', 'Five Stars Makes good coffee with the two filters that comes with it.'),
(991, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-27', 'I got this because I live alone and really got tired of having to clean up my old drip style coffee maker after each use. Also like the 3 tier cup holder and ability to use Ground Coffee in the included nylon basket. Mine takes under 2 minutes from the time I push button to have a cup of coffee. Holds up to 14oz water for your choice of what you are using. OK for 2 people but not convenient if you have many people because of time for each person to get there\'s individually made instead of just pouring out of carafe. A friend of mine has a similar style with a large water reservoir on it, but it would take up more space on my limited kitchen counter. Only takes a couple of uses to know how much water to use for your type and darkness of coffees.'),
(992, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-27', 'they loved this toaster oven I bought it as a gift  and they loved it'),
(993, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-10', 'GREAT BUY SUPRISINGLY .....FROM INEXPENSVE PRICE - THIS UNIT WORKS FANTASTIC'),
(994, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-29', 'Four Stars toaster toast bread evenly almost everytime...'),
(995, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-09', 'Four Stars works great'),
(996, 10, 1, 3, '2015-12-01', 'Three Stars ok'),
(997, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-04', 'i am very happy with the purchase got this for my wife as xmas present.  i am very happy with the purchase. only had it for a few works but works great. i set it on setting 3 for my toast and it is evenly toasted. have not tried a bagel or english muffin yet.'),
(998, 2, 1, 1, '2015-07-12', 'DO NOT BUY. This is a fire hazard. ... DO NOT BUY. This is a fire hazard. The oven started smoking with a strong odor of plastic burning soon after turning it on for the first time.'),
(999, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-15', 'Four Stars Use it daily for breakfast smoothies.'),
(1000, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-24', 'Doesn\'t blend well at all. Doesn\'t crush ice. ... Doesn\'t blend well at all. Doesn\'t crush ice. I had to shake it to move Ice or fruit away from blade for the blade to spin properly.'),
(1001, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-10', 'works great. is as described works great.is as described.coffee taste great.'),
(1002, 6, 1, 3, '2015-06-21', 'Nice Toaster works great, excellent heating and quiet. The look of the toaster is nice and modern and for the price you can\'t beat it. Loving it.'),
(1003, 6, 1, 4, '2016-01-04', 'four star I like this toaster'),
(1004, 8, 1, 4, '2014-07-15', 'Nice addition to my kitchen I enjoy it. It gets the job done pretty well and very fast. As long as you take good care of it, you shouldn\'t have any problem with this product.'),
(1005, 3, 1, 4, '2015-09-01', 'It lasted a long time... I had this toaster over for 7 years.  Used daily.  AT LEAST 2x a day.  We dont have a microwave so we used this oven to reheat food, cook potatoes, cook chicken breasts, cook pork chops and steaks and toast bread. Basically it got used breakfast, lunch and dinner. It did not die on us.  We tossed it out by accident.  Long story. Pros: *durable. *easy to use. *no major problems. Cons: *You cannot clean the heating element.  I still cant figure out how to cook sweet potatoes without getting the syrup on the heating element. I started putting the sweet potatoes on rack and then halfway through the cycle running over and putting foil underneath when I hear them sizzle. *Once you get something on the heating element you will smell burnt food for sometime while using the toaster.  It will eventually fade away. *The labels came off in year 1. *slow cooking times for a small oven.  I think that the door was not shutting properly near the end though... *it looked terrible at the end.  It never really cleaned up properly.  When I tried getting the burnt stuff off of the oven - it scratched.  The stainless steel looks terrible when dirty.  Boo.. Overall it did the job and lasted a long time.  It still worked even when it was discarded so who knows how long it would have gone?'),
(1006, 3, 1, 5, '2015-11-10', 'so far it seems nice. When we use it we will update, so far it seems nice.'),
(1007, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-12', 'I like the smaller size and the crumb tray that pulls ... I like the smaller size and the crumb tray that pulls out for cleaning.  I\'ve looked at a lot of toaster ovens and found that this suited my needs best.'),
(1008, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'Don\'t spend hundreds Best item for the price'),
(1009, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-30', 'Would recommend. Like being able to make a pot. Just a mug or will fit a travel cup. Very versatile.'),
(1010, 7, 3, 4, '2015-01-05', 'I just love the way this works. Cheaper than the other brands. Would like it to hold more water but for the price it\'s great.'),
(1011, 6, 1, 1, '2014-12-19', '2 strikes & you\'re out!! This is the second toaster I\'m returning to Amazon. Neither toasts evenly. The coils only half light on both sides of a 4 slice toaster. This is the only small appliance I\'ve bought by Cuisinart that is a piece of junk. No other way to put it. Look elsewhere!!'),
(1012, 12, 1, 1, '2014-12-15', 'I would not recommend this product to anyone The first one went back because when the door was opened the whole oven tipped forward. The door had too much resistance and did not open all the way. We have a new one and I think its also going back for the same reasons, I would not recommend this product to anyone, its quality is poor at best. Amazon has stood behind it.'),
(1013, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-29', 'Four Stars coffee taste fine'),
(1014, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'Excellent purchase We like the size of this toaster.  It nicely fits 2 relatively large bagels and toasts them to perfection.  It also allows us to bake our favorite \'cheesy-egg\' mini pan dishes.  It works as advertised, and we are very glad we purchased it.'),
(1015, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-19', 'Great Oven and saves energy I have used the model by Black and Decker for about Thirty years. It seems to be ready for renewal every 5 to six years presently on a 7 year one.. It has saved me much much money instead of a big Oven verses a small six slice toaster Oven. But this size Oven bakes a cake ,Meat loaf, Pizza, six slices of toast, any 13 by 9 baking pan. Homemade Macaroni and cheese. Multiple uses....Great Oven and saves energy....Go Green with this toaster oven....'),
(1016, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-22', 'No cooking timer - useless. No cooking timer.  Cheap inexact dials.  So many others that have a timer and are less flimsy.  Walkaway.'),
(1017, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-27', 'Four Stars very good!'),
(1018, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-15', 'Five Stars Works great...'),
(1019, 9, 1, 5, '2016-06-24', 'Five Stars Very pleased - does a great job keeping coffee hot.'),
(1020, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-25', 'Accurate, good, small oven The oven seemed small when I received it. Upon using it I found it could handle most everything I use a toaster oven for. I am not fond of the timer, having to turn it past 10 then back for less time. That\'s a hassle. Overall good value, good product.'),
(1021, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-15', 'I really like this coffee pot I really like this coffee pot. We sill it up the night before and program it to be ready when we get up. The one thing that is not clear was that it does drain the entire tank each time it runs...so you can not select to brew a half pot unless you only fill up half the water.'),
(1022, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-06', 'I\'d buy it again! After my last coffee maker died I thought about purchasing a more expensive one than this one but because it had good reviews and was not expensive I figured I\'d try it. I haven\'t been disappointed! I\'m not a coffee connoisseur but I won\'t drink just any coffee and this coffee maker has been reliable with near daily use. I\'d recommend it.'),
(1023, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-13', 'Love this coffee maker, just the perfect size for a camper. Takes up no room at all. Super fast delivery!'),
(1024, 12, 1, 3, '2014-10-10', 'not durable it was an ok toaster for 3 years, but it didnt hold up.  the mechanism to hold the bread down stopped working.  i figured that it was breadcrumbs so  i tried opening up the unit and cleaning it,  couldnt access the mechanism without major surgery.  tried shaking and tapping the unit to maybe dislodge some breadcrumbs or whatever else was keeping the mechanism from working........nothing worked.  gave up and bought a 4 slice black and decker toaster oven as a replacement.'),
(1025, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-29', 'A great upgrade! We have enjoyed the upgrade to this new machine K250! The additional size water reservoir is more convenient & the coffee maker does warm up alot faster when turning on. Also, it is beneficial to have the option to use the carafe! We like the option for a larger 10oz cup size however, it still does not dispense enough to fill a Large size coffee mug which would be preferred! If that were available we would give it x5 stars!!!!!'),
(1026, 4, 1, 3, '2016-11-23', 'Miss the old GE Toast-R-Oven with the popup door! I guess I expected more, like others, the toast setting is affected by how many times you make toast in a session, i.e. first slices undertoast, later ones overtoast. That tells me it is controlled by a timer, not a heat sensor. Now I noticed one of the bottom elements has warped/drooped down, and it I think, touching the bottom of the oven. That can\'t be too safe, and is probably not doing the countertop underneath any good. I don\'t know if its worth trying to get any warranty replacement, as most of the time by the time you pay shipping and fees, you can buy a new one.However I may take it to Bed, Bath & Beyond, and see if they will replace/return it for me gratis.'),
(1027, 5, 1, 1, '2015-04-02', 'Wasn\'t thrilled with it, but it worked... until it died 5 months later! Wasn\'t thrilled with it, but it worked... very slowly!  5 months later and it won\'t turn on anymore.  Will not reorder!'),
(1028, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-16', 'Great coffee good price and fast shipping.'),
(1029, 8, 1, 5, '2015-11-08', 'Five Stars Great starter pot for someone.  These were donated to a neighborhood that was destroyed by wildfires.'),
(1030, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-07', 'I have had one at home for quite some time and like the unit very much I recently ordered one of these for our office. Small office 4 employees. I have had one at home for quite some time and like the unit very much. It does have a heat plate to keep the coffee warm, but the coffee is self contained with very little heat escape and requires much less heating than a standard glass carafe but the burner on this unit does run at 115 F so it can burn the coffee specially when the coffee levels are low. Since the burner is direct contact with the coffee it is important to keep the burner clean. Once it starts to get a little carbon build up it will get worse much quicker. I always try to make sure the unit is turned off when the coffee levels are low which brings me to my next point. The fuel gauge - this unit uses something very similar to a fuel gauge to display how much coffee is in the unit. It is a little bit hokey. The speed at which the needle goes from full to half is much slower than from half to empty and can be a little misleading. Using an over sized coffee mug, roughly 3 cups, it takes 3 fills to go from full to half, then 1 fill from half to empty. Also when the coffee levels are low the coffee dispenses much slower. Once you know this however, it is fine. We replaced Hamilton Beach Brew Station with this Cuisinart DCC-3000 and I find it much easier to work with. On the Hamilton Beach, the container used to hold the coffee (after it is brewed) is also the same container used to fill the unit with water. You have to make sure it is thoroughly rinsed and clean between each brew. You also have to pour the water back into the unit which always results in water all over the counter. The Cuisinart has a completely separate water tank which is easily removed, filled, and returned with no water anywhere but the sink. This unit brews quickly and quietly and looks very nice. This one came with the basket filter whereas the one I have at home did not so that is a plus. It is very easy to clean between brewing and over all very simple to use.'),
(1031, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-25', 'Can\'t live without this toaster oven! I am single and live in South Florida where it\'s hot year-round. Not having to fire-up my huge regular oven everyday is not only a time-saver, but a huge energy saver too. I\'ve had a couple other brands of toaster ovens before buying this Black & Decker model but they don\'t even compare in quality and functionality. I have had mine now for almost 5 years and it gets use EVERY day at least once. I\'ve used it so much now in fact that all the letters have rubbed off above the buttons - but thankfully becuase I use it so much, I know exactly what every button does//says. I have made whole (smaller) turkeys, chickens, pizzas, baked potatoes, cakes, pies, fritattas and pastries - I absolutely LOVE that it has convection too! I can make thawed seasoned boneless skinless chicken breasts -cooked at 395 (f) degrees, set the timer for 14 minutes, hit the convection button.... after microwave steaming my veggies and taking the dogs outside for a wee  POOF - dinner is done! I\'ve even bought myself some additional toaster oven sized pans, like muffin tins, small cookie sheets, and a new broiler pan. I hardly write reviews, but I am so in love with my toaster oven I want everyone to have this model - I absolutely LOVE it!!'),
(1032, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'This has been a excellent toaster oven This has been a excellent toaster oven. I have used this oven on an almost daily basis for over a year. It is so easy and I can make almost anything in it. I am typically cooking for myself and I and have found this oven to be more than adequate. This oven is super easy to clean. I am happy that I bought it and think you would too.'),
(1033, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-17', 'Five Stars Love this Keurig.  Color is true to picture.  Great for our camper.  Size is perfect.'),
(1034, 3, 1, 3, '2016-08-17', 'You better have good eyesight and be quick Contrary to the image of the oven on the Amazon page, it does not have a lighted display.  Rather, it is black characters on dull gray background making it difficult to read under ordinary lighting conditions.  The labels for the buttons are very small and the up/down buttons aren\'t labeled, they only have barely visible triangular indentations.  I copied the image from the Amazon page and cropped and enlarged the image of the button layout and posted it on a cabinet door above the oven.  Functionally it seems to be performing as expected, although you had better know what temperature and time to set and how to set it quickly because if you don\'t get it done in 10 seconds you have to start the whole procedure over again.  The shortcomings weren\'t enough to pack it up and send it back but sometimes I wish we had.'),
(1035, 10, 1, 2, '2015-01-25', 'Time consuming Hate having to hold the button.'),
(1036, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'I love my coffee Read the reviews and unlike many I am not fancy coffee professional; however, I love my coffee! This is the best coffee maker I have ever purchased! It brews really fast and I like the lever you press to dispense the coffee as opposed to my old maker that your cup pushed the button to release the coffee. The light that comes on when dispensing the coffee is very helpful too!'),
(1037, 2, 1, 2, '2016-03-02', 'Toaster is not SILVER - it\'s BLACK with silver accents This product could be fine, but I\'m really irritated that the title of the toaster is SILVER, and the photos only show a silver toaster - and it turns out the body and sides are black. Had Amazon offered different display photos, I would have easily caught the issue and not purchased it. Now I have to go to the trouble of sending it back.'),
(1038, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-15', 'Five Stars Great little coffee maker!'),
(1039, 4, 1, 1, '2016-03-23', 'Designed to Fail, Don\'t Waste Your Money I purchased this toaster oven less than 3 years ago. The two bottom elements have failed because they were so poorly made. It is sad that a brand name like Cuisinart has chosen a POOR manufacturing partner.'),
(1040, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-03', 'Five Stars I use it everyday.'),
(1041, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-29', 'Five Stars The best. Although the steam can cause a stain under your cabinet.'),
(1042, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-31', 'Love our Keurig K250 ! Enjoying our Keurig K250 !  So easy and fast and the coffee is so great !'),
(1043, 2, 1, 2, '2016-04-12', 'Overly-Complicated Overly-complicated controls.  Tiny print on controls requires reading glasses for anyone over 50.  Useless icons on controls take up space that could be used to enlarge the print.  Set three knobs to toast, reset the same three knobs to bake.  On the other hand, it requires almost no time to preheat, and because of this, it is much faster than using the regular oven for say, two slices of pizza.'),
(1044, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-28', 'Five Stars A perfect machine!'),
(1045, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-05', 'A Great Coffee Maker! I love Keurig! I can\'t really give a thorough review as I got this for my son and future DIL for their shower.  But, they have told me that they are in love with it and have experienced no problems. The turquoise color is very pretty and matches their kitchen perfectly. I have a Keurig Vue...have had it for about 5 years and have never had any problems whatsoever.  I\'m jealous of theirs...LOL...I see an upgrade coming soon. :-)'),
(1046, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-21', 'Piece of crap Owned this for less than 5 years and only used if to make TOAST- just stopped working.  Manual offers no troubleshooting and it\'s out of warranty.  When I looked online for help I found an entire site dedicated to complaining about Cuisinart\'s lack of quality.  I just moved and gave away my other toaster thinking this one would last longer because it was not as old as the other.  Big Mistake.  Save your money and buy something else.'),
(1047, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-19', 'Better than Cuisenart!! Great coffee maker!! Replaced Cuisenart that broke down after 7 years but didn\'t want to pay $90.00 for another one. I like how this Hamilton Beach allows you to fill a separate container and always know how much water is in that \"tank\". The function of BOLD is terrific or even just 1 cup!!  The panel display is easier to maneuver if you end up unplugging it for some reason (to reprogram). Have had this for a month and I love this coffee maker!!!'),
(1048, 3, 1, 2, '2014-06-13', 'High Hopes, Low Results With a little more effort, this could be a decent product.  It is attractive, it heats well, and temperatures seem to be accurate.  However, there are several flaws. Within a few weeks the function labels began to wear off so that a year later, they are almost completely blank.  If you haven\'t memorized the function keys (and there are many) you\'re out of luck. They may as well have been written in pencil.  The outside of the oven gets extremely hot, especially the handle!  That\'s a safety hazard.  Also, the oven door, when opened has no catch; it just drops down with a bang onto the counter.  Overall it is a disappointment.'),
(1049, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-25', 'Five Stars Performs quite well, and is a pleasing design using very little space on the counter.'),
(1050, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-20', 'Glad I read the reviews Im impressed!  Glad I read the reviews.  Great little coffee maker.'),
(1051, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-30', 'a lot of people say theyre great and then you look at the one star reviews ... i spent weeks looking over amazon for a coffee maker that had universally positive reviews. for someone addicted to reviews buying a coffee maker is a nightmare. a lot of people say theyre great and then you look at the one star reviews of people complaining they dont get hot enough to make a good pot. well i feel like this thing gets plenty hot. ive had it for over a year and no problems. just a good as it was on day 1. i love the removable water reservoir. this coffee maker fits perfectly under our cabinets and i dont have to move it to get the water reservoir out. it looks really nice as long as you dont inspect it with a microscope and examine the cheap plastic. it matches my stainless appliances. and the timer feature is a godsend. when i think about how good i am at shopping on amazon, this is one of my shining moments. go me'),
(1052, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Good Price I simply love this product!!!'),
(1053, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-26', 'Great coffee maker This coffee maker is great I\'ve used it about every day for the last eight months and haven\'t had a issue yet. The back water chamber is detachable for easy filling and cleaning. It also has three brewing options which are very nice, and three temperature selections for you to choose from.'),
(1054, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-17', 'Five Stars love love .... PRICE BEAT MACYS PENNYS KOHLS!!!'),
(1055, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-12', 'great toaster, love all the options and style great toaster,love all the options and style.very happy with it.'),
(1056, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-14', 'Just one of the best in my book This coffee maker is a no frills, but very solid coffee maker. Nicely engineered, and just what we like about a regular coffee maker.'),
(1057, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Just my Comments I use my K250, 2.0 in conjunction with using the ECO-FILL 2.0 Coffee Filter.  Why the ECO-FILL Deluxe filter?  We have a local coffee shop that has 20+ different kinds of beans.  I use their darkest bean ground to \"Fine,\" in a one pound bag at a time.  How simple is that with using the coffee type I prefer and most cost effective over buying K cups.  The coffee taste using the ECO-Fill Deluxe is perfect for me.  The local coffee shop had tested the Keurig and said the stainless steel meshed filters work the best for these machines, when using your own coffee. I registered my K250 for their one year warranty.  Then they e-mailed me a special offer, with an assigned code, to buy 92 cups.  I bought their Green Mountain Dark Magic Extra Bold with free shipping.  Why did I buy some pods,....just b/c. I thought I would pass along my comments.  Enjoy your K250.'),
(1058, 5, 1, 3, '2014-07-10', 'Its a good coffee maker Its a good coffee maker, however we received it with broken pieces to begin with.  I wasn\'t about to deal with the hassle of exchanging it, I just can\'t use the lid to the coffee pot as it is broken.'),
(1059, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'You mean I can enjoy the whole pot before it tastes scorched I can change the burner temp? You mean I can enjoy the whole pot before it tastes scorched? Awesome! wheels? Removable water reservoir I can easily take to the fridge for filtered water? Nice work HB R&D.'),
(1060, 5, 1, 2, '2016-08-28', 'Burns the coffee I love the design and functionality of this unit, but the coffee always comes out burnt! I tried to change grounds, thinking it was that, but the coffee always tasted awful... Finally got a french press and realized it was burnt taste. I wish I could have realized this earlier so I could switch it out, but it\'s been about 3 months now.'),
(1061, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-23', 'Love this coffee maker Love this coffee maker.  I really wanted a \"front load\" unit - I always hated having to pull my coffee maker from out under the cabinet to set it up.  This unit has a front load compartment for the coffee grounds that swings out.  Even better, the water compartment detaches like a Keurig from the back and you can fill it easily at the faucet rather than filling the pot and trying to pour it in.  Great pot for such a reasonable price.'),
(1062, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-23', 'A no brainer! Such an amazing product! Heats up nice and quick, and I have my coffee within 5 minutes of waking up :) A nice and quiet product, I do wish the water reservoir was larger, as we have to refill about once a day. The drop tray releases extremely easily, which at first i didn\'t love, but now it\'s perfect for when I brew into my tall travel mug! I received this product free from Influenster to test and review, but I highly recommend it for anyone out there!'),
(1063, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Great Blender, Bottle makes it very convenient This is a great blender. I have used mine for years (Id say 6 or 7 years) blending protein shakes in the morning almost daily!! Doing the math, thats over 2,000 shakes!! I add tons of fruit, protein powder, milk, and ice, and this blender has never and still never has an issue blending! I don\'t really use many of the other features of this blender so I will not speak on them BUT if you are looking for a blender that will last for YEARS with daily use.. THIS IS YOUR BLENDER'),
(1064, 12, 1, 2, '2014-10-13', 'very outdated look more like 1970\'s nosleekness like pic very outdated look  more like 1970\'s  nosleekness like pic dictates'),
(1065, 6, 1, 3, '2015-01-09', 'Three Stars it is ok for this price.'),
(1066, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-08', 'quality that makes me come back for more a 4-slice toaster that I would gladly use over and over again as long as there is bread and electricity available.'),
(1067, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-01', 'good product. Good reliable appliance for the size. I would buy it again'),
(1068, 3, 1, 5, '2015-10-07', 'Five Stars Thank you very much I am very pleased with this product VERY HAPPY ..... !!!!!!!!!! 1000% satisfied ........'),
(1069, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-16', 'We love the new Keurig We love the new Keurig, the way it talks to you.The video available to watch on internet is extremely helpful. A few complaints tho,there is no clock,and no timer to preheat the water before you awake.thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review'),
(1070, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-23', 'SUPER TOASTER GREAT TOASTER, I HIGHLY RECOMMEND.'),
(1071, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-21', 'It worked perfectly at first. But after two months ... It worked perfectly at first. But after two months of usage, it cannot blend things anymore! I use it to make green smoothie and now it leaves large chunks of vegetables unblended. I contacted customer service and they ask $9.99 shipping cost for a replacement! The whole unit only costs $14 when I bought it. So buy if you only intend to use for two months or buy every two months.'),
(1072, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-19', 'It was a gift A gift for my son who has wanted a toaster oven for a while now. He is happy with it thus far. He has only had it 3 months.'),
(1073, 6, 1, 2, '2015-10-19', 'This is one of those moment when you think this is just stupid, miscommunication and misrepresentation I purchased this toaster for my mother.  We returned the first one because it would only toast on one side.  Amazon sent a replacement, and same situation.  My mom called Cuisinart.  They told her that she has to use two slices of bread in the toaster.  It doesn\'t say that in the description on Amazon nor anywhere on the box. She certainly isn\'t the only person in the world who makes one piece of toast.  We\'ve both had toasters in the past that was marked \"one slice\" on one slot, so you knew that if you were making one slice that was the side to use. This is one of those moment when you think this is just stupid, miscommunication and misrepresentation.  Come on, Cuisinart is a large company - you can\'t describe a toaster properly?  We are sure this has happened before, because when mom told the Cuisinart representative the problem, he immediately knew the answer.  This second toaster was returned, and a different brand purchased - hopefully, no more \"one slice\" issues!!'),
(1074, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-14', 'love!!! Love this oven. Got one 7 years ago. Finally went up. Tried others but hated. So happy to find this one again'),
(1075, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-10', 'Five Stars It works great.'),
(1076, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Works great for me Works great for me!  Keeps my coffee hot and contrary to others, it doesn\'t leak, easy to fill and would buy it again!'),
(1077, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-09', 'it\'s smaller than a very old model that we used to have (also Black & Decker) We are amazed how fast this makes the toasts compared to the older model Black & Decker toaster we used to have.  It\'s also more compact.  I really like the compactness and how much faster it takes to toast.  Love it!!!'),
(1078, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-09', 'so much better tasting, than stovetop or regular processing, boiling..'),
(1079, 3, 1, 2, '2016-06-08', 'We purchased this toaster oven November 2015. It has ... We purchased this toaster oven November 2015.  It has worked well although I do notice the outside gets very hot and it is slow to heat up.  Today, it just stopped heating.  7 months and it\'s not working.  I\'m not sure I will even try to return it under the warranty.'),
(1080, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-25', '5 stars happy purchase .'),
(1081, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-04', 'This is a gift from heaven for coffee drinkers I bought this coffee maker to be able to make my Spanish coffee before and after work. So far, so good! I\'m very happy and satisfied with this product!'),
(1082, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-24', 'Five Stars Cute and convenient.'),
(1083, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-31', 'Five Stars works great'),
(1084, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-28', 'Nice and Easy to use! Great coffee maker.  Love that the door swing open to put coffee grinds in.  Also love the water reservoir in the back.  The coffee taste great at light or bold option.  It makes coffee quickly.'),
(1085, 12, 1, 1, '2014-05-15', 'not the best Looks nice but the oven part is small which is nice if you don\'t have much counter space but it doesn\'t toast evenly we used it for about 6 months and then replaced.'),
(1086, 9, 1, 4, '2015-08-14', 'It takes up a good deal of space This would probably be ok for someone else, not for us.  It takes up a good deal of space.  The coffee water didn\'t stay warm.  I don\'t know if this particular coffeemaker was defective or was supposed to be that way.  It is nice to get a cup at a time,  and the water holder is removable for easy filling and cleaning.'),
(1087, 5, 1, 3, '2014-12-08', 'It is a nice coffee pot It is a nice coffee pot, the down side is the steam comes directly from the top so if it is under an enclosed area there is no place for the steam to escape problem is solved by moving it out every evening,  I use the auto turn on.  I find the fill tank is hard to remove so I just use a measuring cup to fill.  The coffee pot makes hot coffee and on time!  I would buy a different style next time though.'),
(1088, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-20', 'Satisfied so far.... I purchased this product directly from Keurig and had to have it replaced almost immediately because of a faulty touch screen. However, the customer service was excellent and the replacement came in the mail very fast. Since then, it\'s worked very well and I haven\'t had any issues. I like that it makes my coffee quickly, has the additional size options and when I signed up for emails from Keurig, they started sending me offers for discounts on pods all the time. All in all, pretty satisfied. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(1089, 7, 3, 1, '2015-08-17', 'Bought this coffee maker to use in our RV. Brought it home and discovered that it does not accept reusable/refillable K-Cups. Can only use prepackaged K-Cups. Back to Walmart goes this one.'),
(1090, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-11', 'best coffe pot ever i can set it up to ... best coffe pot ever i can set it up to make a new pot even before the coffee is gone once gone i put it in automatic & its ready to brew the next morning  (make shore to empty pot first or it will overflow)'),
(1091, 4, 1, 1, '2016-06-28', 'Not worth it... Only have had this toaster oven for a couple of months and unfortunately it isn\'t working. It seems like there\'s an issue with the knob to change your settings (bake, toast, etc.) which shuts the unit off completely. I also don\'t like the fact that this oven doesn\'t have a timer so when I put something in, I have to set a timer so that it doesn\'t burn.'),
(1092, 1, 1, 2, '2016-04-08', 'I am a pretty good reader but somehow missed that you MUST use ... The reason for two stars: I am a pretty good reader but somehow missed that you MUST use k cups with the round Keurig brewed label. No exceptions. If you use a k pod that says Keurig but doesn\'t have the round Keurig label and the words, \"Keurig brewed\" you will get an error and molten coffee grounds spewing out of your machine. OK coffee for a k cup machine. Not as good as brewed coffee but getting a quick cup makes up for that.'),
(1093, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-23', 'Well thought out coffee maker Coffee maker which is very easy to use. No worries about scalding oneself when refilling as the water container slips off easily and the container for the coffee grounds are in a swing container.  Great features.'),
(1094, 4, 1, 2, '2016-10-21', 'nice but needs a muffler for its alert tone nice toaster oven...toasts pretty quick and gets up to temp quickly and good capacity for not too big of a footprint.  Sadly, however the the alert beep tone is WAY TOO LOUD.  I mean like don\'t trying toasting something while someone else is sleeping within 30 feet of the unit, even with doors. I returned the unit.'),
(1095, 5, 1, 3, '2015-11-06', 'Three Stars just wasn\'t that great and went to the bunn'),
(1096, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-18', 'Heats up fast and looks great. Use it quite a bit Heats up fast and looks great. Use it quite a bit. Warning though: when you are opening up the box use caution and probably avoid scissors. I went to slide the tape open on the top of the box with scissors and now have a scratch on the top of the toaster oven. There was nothing protecting it unfortunately.'),
(1097, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-12', 'This little oven is awesome! It\'s not just a toaster oven This little oven is awesome! It\'s not just a toaster oven. It is an actual convection oven that also works as a toaster. Baked two loaves of cornbread that came out better than perfect. And, for the price? Please, this thing is a steal!'),
(1098, 4, 1, 1, '2016-08-09', 'There is no happy median for the settings Toaster lightness control is worthless, Have to stand by and watch closely to keep from burning toast, bagels etc. When you adjust it to  lighter just a smidgen it causes you to have to recycle the toaster, if you increase it to get it darker it burns the toast.  There is no happy median for the settings. Would not recommend this to any one.  Looking for a new one at this time. So feed up with this piece of junk.'),
(1099, 9, 1, 5, '2016-06-07', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker!  Easy to use, makes great coffee!'),
(1100, 11, 1, 5, '2015-01-02', 'Perfect Perfect'),
(1101, 5, 1, 4, '2016-07-11', 'excellent coffee maker classy design and works like a charm.'),
(1102, 9, 1, 4, '2016-02-08', 'Well Designed Love the way you can prepare the coffee before you need it and then switch it on, enjoy a cup, and save the rest well heated in the interior. Then when it is time to clean, it is super easy. Best coffee pot ever.'),
(1103, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Five Stars Extremely useful and so efficient! Love the design and color. Flavor of coffee excellent!'),
(1104, 5, 1, 3, '2016-08-01', 'Three Stars Can\'t make 10+ cups without too many grounds getting into the carafe.'),
(1105, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-04', 'Didnt expect this would be as useful and last as long as it has Didnt expect this would be as useful and last as long as it has. For the price a gem. I use sometime twice a day and it was only suppose to be a quick fix for work coffee for my husband.  I also waste a lot less coffee and it is fast.'),
(1106, 6, 1, 4, '2016-10-16', 'Four Stars works great, brownness settings on both sides are the same. on both side are the same.'),
(1107, 6, 1, 4, '2016-10-20', 'Four Stars IT\'s a good, solid, reliable toaster. You won\'t regret buying it.'),
(1108, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-04', 'Four Stars What do you want, it toasts. Big whoop.'),
(1109, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-14', 'The best little oven This is the best little toaster oven. There\'s no need to spend any more money on a toaster oven. It looks nice, works perfectly and the whole family uses it all day every day.'),
(1110, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-12', 'worth the money for under 30 bucks does the job i made toast heated sandwhichs hot wings and chicken nuggets and done a pretty good job has alot of different settings like a oven which i like'),
(1111, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-14', 'Five Stars Love having this'),
(1112, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-25', 'Five Stars it is very good for the price'),
(1113, 3, 1, 4, '2016-04-26', 'This is a great toaster oven and definitely more efficient than heating the ... This is a great toaster oven and definitely more efficient than heating the entire large oven for just one piece chicken or small meal. It\'s pretty large, so we don\'t keep it on the countertop all of the time. We really like the digital display, so we know exactly how much time is left/temperature. Definitely happy with this purchase.'),
(1114, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-14', 'Great coffeemaker I love this coffeepot. Keeps the coffee really hot and does not scorch it.'),
(1115, 3, 1, 3, '2014-06-30', 'Oven is good. Cord is way too short Oven is good.  Cord is way too short.'),
(1116, 10, 1, 4, '2015-08-06', 'Works for smoothies/shakes, but not meant to blend hard stuff This blender works fine for smoothies and shakes. However, it is not meant for blending other things, particularly harder items, such as soaked lentils, batter, soup veggies, or making chutneys. You also have to add a certain amount of liquid to get the blender to work. So for making thick consistencies, this won\'t work. It\'s likely because the motor seems not strong enough. But other than that, I\'ve had it for 2 years and it\'s worked fine for making to-go smoothies. You have to go easy on it and pulse for a few seconds at a time because otherwise you start feeling friction/strain in the motor.'),
(1117, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-27', 'From almond butter to solid fruits, you got it! Still working as amazingly as it was the day it arrived. Fresh out the box we cleaned it, and make a protein shake. Used almond milk, almond butter, half a banana and some Optimum Nutrition chocolate powder, and it blended it all perfectly! Do NOT expect to just hold the button down, that\'s not how this works. You must use it in short little bursts. Well worth the money, that\'s for sure!'),
(1118, 12, 1, 4, '2016-12-30', 'I love the concept however I do wish the oven part ... I love the concept however I do wish the oven part was a little taller. but it definitely saves space on the counter!.'),
(1119, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'happy customer its perfect.  heats up quick.  looks nice.  best coffee in seconds'),
(1120, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-04', 'Four Stars does what it is supposed to do'),
(1121, 5, 1, 2, '2016-05-03', 'Worked for a month- then POP I purchased this coffee maker a little less than a month ago (April 2016).  It was shipped well, made decent coffee, easy to use/fill/clean... but I will now be returning it (just under the 1 month deadline).  Unfortunately it is not very well built and the top panel (by the buttons) popped off.  Two adults that drink a pot a day, nothing excessive. Instead of going through Hamilton Beach, I used Amazon\'s fantastic customer service to get the refund going right away.'),
(1122, 12, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'Five Stars Does everything we need it to do in half the space.'),
(1123, 10, 1, 3, '2015-12-12', 'Three Stars Kinda cheap. Did the trick but didn\'t last very long.'),
(1124, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-30', 'I wish I had spent another $10 and gotten a better one. the size is good for us Buttons are very small and hard to read. I would not buy it again. I wish I had spent another $10 and gotten a better one. the size is good for us.... we warm up pizza in it and make toast mainly but it\'s not much of an oven if you want to cook a meal in it.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1125, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'good for a shake or mixed drink For the price, its good if all you want to do is make something akin to a shake, such as protein powder and milk. Soft vegetables like an onion might be okay. This is a small, single serve unit.'),
(1126, 8, 1, 4, '2016-09-29', 'Four Stars Quick and easy. I wish it had a feature to stop coffee flow when the pot is removed.'),
(1127, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-20', 'Five Stars A better improvement since our last one. Water easier to add.'),
(1128, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-09', 'great toaster w/ space for heating up a pizza slice! This toaster is so great I\'ve bought it 3 times (there wasn\'t a problem with it- we just moved cross country 3x and it\'s so inexpensive we decided to re-buy rather than ship it out). As a toaster, it toasts everything nice & toasty and very quickly. As a toaster oven it is the PERFECT size for a slice or 2 of pizza, or to roast a can of garbanzo beans. It\'s small (slightly larger than an average toaster) and has always fit nicely in our small apartment kitchens. It\'s a basic item, but it does everything it is supposed to do well, and that is great!.'),
(1129, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-12', 'Yassssss THIS IS THE BEST TOASTER OVEN EVER I LOVE THIS THING I USE IT EVERYDAY'),
(1130, 8, 1, 1, '2016-09-11', 'Packing was bad Receive the item broken.'),
(1131, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-28', 'Dangerous product I have had the same heating element problems. Now it is turning itself on and off as you walk by it. Into the garbage before it burns my house down.'),
(1132, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Thank you Keriug for an amazing product and FREE K CUPS! We are extremely happy with our new Keruig 2.0. I love the sleek style which gives me more counter space. I can still choose cup size and everything else that we did with our old Keruig with the exception of choosing water tempature. Another plus is that there is no taking in and out the old k cup holder when you want to use fresh grounds in a re usable k cup. It\'s just one place where the  both k cups fit perfect. Now here is the best part when you register your Keruig online the send you a code for two free boxes of k cups, yes that\'s right 2 free boxes. Thank you Keriug for the free boxes!'),
(1133, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-28', 'One-sided exaggerations? I thought the reviews about this toaster only toasting one side were exaggerated. How could that be possible? I was replacing a Cuisinart that had worked great for me for 14 years. Well, the reviewers were not exaggerating. When one side of the toaster only toasted one side of the bread, I thought I could live with it if at least the other side toasted both sides. No such luck. I\'m returning today. I was pleasantly surprised how easy Amazon made the return process.'),
(1134, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-11', 'Five Stars WORKS GREAT.'),
(1135, 7, 3, 1, '2016-01-16', 'I need a single serve coffee maker since I only drink one cup a day. Bought a Kuerig 2.0, but returned it because of a very strong plastic smell and taste, even after all the suggestions I read on cleaning it thoroughly. Then I saw this Hamilton Beach, and decided for the price ($39.99) it was worth a chance. Well, it worked great for about 2 weeks. Then I had company stay with me over the weekend, and I did as the instructions said... wait 2 minutes before brewing a new cup. Well, it never would make another cup correctly... and I tried using both the Kcups and the basket of regular coffee. I decided to return it to the store but found the box apparently got thrown out so I am stuck it. Anyway, I have found the main problem is it does not allow the water in correctly. No water, no coffee! One morning it would not accept any water at all so while messing around trying to make it work, I powered it on, and darn if it didn\'t \"open up\" and let the water in. I immediately turned it off, and added more water to make a cup just fine. So apparently it has sensor problems! I am sure one day soon it will never work again! Another complaint is it is very noisy and will make a mess on your counter top. It\'s such a shame companies no longer take pride in their production of products so I will have to be very diligent in making sure I keep the boxes for returning, if need be.'),
(1136, 5, 1, 3, '2016-07-05', 'Coffee maker works just fine. We love the simplicity of the functions and ... Coffee maker works just fine. We love the simplicity of the functions and the design overall.  Then first time is was cleaning by simply wiping around where the basket is placed, the face plate that covers the buttons and diplay screen came off.  The plastic around the screws that hold it in place broke.  We had this product for less than a week.  It does work really well and the damage is just cosmetic.  We gave this 3 stars because the overall quality is lacking.  I guess this is what to expect from a mass-produced-in-China product.  Such is the way of most things these days.  Stack-em deep & sell-em cheap.'),
(1137, 7, 3, 5, '2014-11-22', 'Bought this for work. We moved into a new office space with no microwave so zi use this to make coffee, heat water for my AM oatmeal and afternoon cup of noodles. Does the trick and takes no time at all.'),
(1138, 11, 1, 5, '2014-05-09', 'Good value Toasts great, roasted beets great, that\'s all I\'ve done so far,  good size and looks good.  Kind of weird off/on, choose options system but I figured it out.  Probably should have looked at instructions!  Overall like it, glad I went with it instead of the more expensive ones, toaster ovens are pretty basic!'),
(1139, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Perfect - size, pretty quiet and does the job. Perfect for work, love the size and it does the job well!'),
(1140, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-12', 'Don\'t waste your $$$ My second (and LAST) 2.0 just stopped working.  We loved the first Keurig but when the original finally stopped, we purchased this piece of junk.  If you enjoy your cup of coffee in the morning, this unit isn\'t for you since it is never dependable on if it will actually produce a cup of coffee.'),
(1141, 1, 1, 2, '2016-03-11', 'Only 6 oz Disappointed, only goes to six ounces... So basically just two options 4oz or 6 oz.  Really wish they would have said how many ounces it brewed.  My parents bought a similar one and it goes to 10 oz.  Nice color though.'),
(1142, 8, 1, 5, '2016-12-06', 'Five Stars works good.'),
(1143, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-22', 'It is so simple to use. I love it! If it ever wears out, I would go right out and buy one again. I have my own personal coffee brewer.'),
(1144, 6, 1, 5, '2014-05-02', 'Great Toaster This was a Christmas Gift to myself, and I made a great choice. It is easy to use and is a perfect size. I will enjoy using it for a long time to come.'),
(1145, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-20', 'One Star This blender died after a month of using it. I bought a nutri bullet instead.'),
(1146, 4, 1, 2, '2016-02-15', 'Door became very hard to open after a year There is much to like about this.  It\'s a good size.  It was one of the few I could find that had knobs for controls; the rest tended to have electronic controls that reset to defaults after each cook cycle or when it\'s unplugged.  (I had a problem with a previous toaster oven, and an oven that\'s unplugged is not likely to catch on fire.)  The temperature is pretty accurate. Unfortunately, after a year or so, the door degraded.  A lot of the time, I have to tug hard on the door, repeatedly.  This is even more of a problem when the oven is hot and has food in it.  Given the price, I expected it to be easy to use for longer.'),
(1147, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-04', 'I have owned this product for appx 2 months and it is terrible. It leaks, it chooses what amount of coffee it will make, its very noisy and very slow.'),
(1148, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-30', 'Four Stars works well and no problems with dripping while pouring.'),
(1149, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-06', 'Five Stars Love this coffee pot'),
(1150, 6, 1, 4, '2015-05-23', 'Good value for the money It seems to perform satisfactorily.  Haven\'t had it all that long and I\'m still getting used to the settings.'),
(1151, 11, 1, 1, '2014-09-14', 'Not good Not good'),
(1152, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-10', 'Good coffee I got his for my husband.  He enjoys it, and thinks the coffee tastes better.  I don\'t drink coffee so don\'t know.  However, I do note that you can fill all or part of a cup (or any not too high container)  and it is easy to use.  You do not save on cleaning time as, even if it is not poured into a carafe, you still need to clean out the interior containers (which lift out).  My only negative comment is that the cord is way to short to be useful, even backed up to the wall behind the counter, with our plug just a few inches up, the plug could not be reached. Update 2/25/2015 -  I did not give it a five rating due to the cord length, however, a reviewer pointed out in comment 1, that the cord was  about 2 feet long and indeed it is.  The cord was wound pretty tight but knowing the length was there, my husband tried again to get the cord to pull out and succeeded. so I upped the rating to a 5.'),
(1153, 9, 1, 4, '2016-02-23', 'Nice coffee maker Nice coffee maker.  The dispenser outlet could be a little larger, but not a big deal.  Makes wonderful coffee!'),
(1154, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-07', 'A good in-between for entertaining purposes, especially for occasional use. We have a Keurig to do our day to day coffee duties. I\'m fine with it (though not the waste generated from the K-cups) and I think it makes an acceptable cup of coffee for the price. Buying K-cups in bulk, even Starbucks, it\'s only 81 cents a cup.  But, we were using a 10 year old basic Black and Decker 12 cup for our entertaining purposes, something we don\'t do too often. But the last few times we used it, the coffee had a funny taste and there was a moldy smell to the coffeemaker. I knew we needed a new one. I didn\'t want to spend much, I was thinking another under-$35 coffeemaker would suffice.  But you can\'t find them with a stainless carafe, at least not easily, until you spend $50-$70.  My mother has had multiple Bunn\'s over the years and I like them. But you need to leave them plugged in and we didn\'t need that. And the cost for them was a quite a bit more than we wanted to spend. We were at the department store that begins with a K when my wife saw this Cuisnart.  It was more money than we were thinking, but it appeared to fill our need exactly. We bought it there, as we needed it for the evening. It works great and is exactly what we needed. It brewed 12 cups in about 7 minutes. The coffee tasted fine and clean-up is very easy since many of the key pieces come apart to be cleaned.  My only complaint is that I\'m concerned for the durability of the lever that you push. It seems a bit cheap and might be the first thing to go, rendering the machine useless.  Oh, and the Coffee Gauge(tm) is a novelty, but does its task approximately.  If you are a gearhead like myself, think of a car fuel gauge from the 80\'s (specifically GM). That\'s how accurate it is! So, it\'s still new, durability isn\'t a concern and it\'s worked as it should.  It fills our need for an occasional use machine without breaking the bank. If that\'s what you need in a coffeemaker, get this one.'),
(1155, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-17', 'Five Stars Thank you!'),
(1156, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-09', 'Five Stars works great.'),
(1157, 10, 1, 3, '2015-04-04', 'It\'s great for liquids It\'s great for liquids, but add too many frozen things and it really gets stuck. It doesn\'t blend very well. I will need to get a bigger one for smoothies with frozen bananas, blueberries, strawberries, and spinach all together.'),
(1158, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Five Stars __'),
(1159, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-31', 'Five Stars Amazing coffee machine, great for individual coffee or group size. Very quick and useful.'),
(1160, 8, 1, 4, '2016-12-06', 'Nice coffee maker Just the size I need--but doesn\'t have an automatic shutoff!.'),
(1161, 6, 1, 2, '2015-02-25', 'Beware Bagles Biggest problem is with bagles.  On most toasters the setting for bagles means it will toast one side.  This one toasts both sides and it gets old to have a crusty bottom on your bagle.  For the price I would have expected a lot better product from Cuisinart.'),
(1162, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-23', 'Its good! This coffeemaker is really deserving of all the reviews. The basket is in the front, its super easy to take the water tank to the sink, and its easy to set the programmable timer.'),
(1163, 6, 1, 3, '2015-08-11', 'Pretty happy with it. My only complaint is that it easily burns the toast on one side, if only toasting one slice.'),
(1164, 2, 1, 1, '2016-02-15', 'It did not last for too long. I\'ve had ... It did not last for too long. I\'ve had two of the same brand and they both last less than 1 year.'),
(1165, 2, 1, 1, '2015-03-22', 'Returning mine I\'m returning mine as it just barely touched 350 MAX'),
(1166, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-25', 'Love \"defrost\" feature Love \"defrost\" feature!  Must have 2-slices inserted to get even browning ... individual slices will brown on one side and almost burn on second side.'),
(1167, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-29', 'My new favorite kitchen appliance My new favorite kitchen appliance! We don\'t use a microwave and once our son came along people told us we were crazy and that would change. We just purchased this toaster oven and quick food prep has become so much easier!'),
(1168, 12, 1, 3, '2017-01-13', 'Three Stars Returned it.'),
(1169, 2, 1, 4, '2016-07-15', 'but what I\'ve used it for has been just fine. My last one was good for 10 years ... This is my second B and D smaller oven.  Haven\'t had it long, but what I\'ve used it for has been just fine.  My last one was good for 10 years so I expect this will perform the same.  Not a heavy user....mostly toasting, heating leftovers and such.  Not much actually cooking except for the frozen pizza once in awhile.  I like the size, the controls seem much more readable than my old one.  The crumb tray sits inside the oven...which is taking some getting used to...but it\'s fine also.'),
(1170, 8, 1, 1, '2016-02-24', 'junk broke after one time. really?'),
(1171, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-10', 'Great product Bought it for a friend . She loves it.'),
(1172, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-15', 'legit was as advertised.'),
(1173, 3, 1, 4, '2016-07-26', 'REALLY WORKS GREAT except for the DESIGN REALLY WORKS GREAT except for the DESIGN of the handle! This toaster oven does a great job! But there IS a decent learning curve in learning how to use it since it\'s fully programmable,,, kinda wish I had just gone with one with the knob settings..... Also the handle should have been designed with a large curve !!! Because it is straight and if you are not REAL careful when you close the glass lid and you finger touches the top front edge it WILL BURN YOU !!!.'),
(1174, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-10', 'great coffee. What\'s to complain about Very quick delivery, great coffee. What\'s to complain about? I love it. Edit: 4 months later and this coffee pot is still the best one I\'ve ever had. It is SO easy to clean, makes the most amazing coffee and I will never have a different coffee pot. This is the best.'),
(1175, 11, 1, 5, '2015-05-18', 'Five Stars Happy with how it toast and bakes.  Easy to clean.  I would recommend this to anyone.'),
(1176, 12, 1, 1, '2015-01-18', 'Single Worst Amazon Purchase EVER This has been the single worst Amazon purchase I have ever made.  To begin with, the unit is undersized so all of the heating elements are very close to the food (too close).  What this means is that the toaster part of the oven is too narrow for bagels and tends to under toast or over toast with very little margin.  Similarly, the heating element for the oven burns things even when you are watching whatever it is you cook.  And you do have to watch what you cook because there is no timer.  The tray gets jammed easily and the door won\'t close all the way.  The tray itself is cheaply made and does not clean easily.  Also, the bottom rack that collects crumbs is inaccessible for cleaning and tends to accumulate debris because of the awkward design of the tray.  In general, the construction is flimsy and after just two months of use, the toaster lever won\'t stay down any more so you can no longer toast anything.  In every way possible, this has been a disappointing purchase - and I am sure I am leaving things out, but I hope you get the gist - that this is not something you want to be wasting any money on.'),
(1177, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-16', 'Works well. I use it several times a week ... Works well.  I use it several times a week.'),
(1178, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'I like the simplicity of the twist dials over using a ... I read the reviews and was worried about the \"burnt plastic\" smell associated with this product from many users. There was a slight odor the first few uses and it then went away. I like the simplicity of the twist dials over using a keypad. The main use for me is to broil up steaks, and cook up chicken wings. I\'ll also use it to heat up foods and to warm plates. It works fine for me. Very satisfied.'),
(1179, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-07', 'I like this coffee maker I am very happy I chose this one!  I love that I can fill the water resevior by removing it and taking it to the sink  rather than carring my pitcher of water across the kitchen.  The caraf is a bit smaller than the b&d I had but it makes good coffee and the coffee stays hot.'),
(1180, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-11', 'Good basic toaster oven I received my toaster oven today and have used it to make toast, grilled cheese and pizza. I wanted it for these basic things but know that I can use it to cook a lot more. I plan on baking chicken and reheating dishes I\'ve made for dinner. The oven works very well and my toast, gilled cheese and pizza came out perfectly.'),
(1181, 6, 1, 4, '2016-01-31', 'It works nicely. We like the different settings for bagels and ... We have had this toaster for a little over a year.  It works nicely.  We like the different settings for bagels and such.'),
(1182, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-07', 'Great coffee maker, no problems. I\'ve had this one for 6 months, so far no problems. Very user friendly, can\'t get any easier to program. Pours cleanly without a mess. Reservoir comes out to fill at the sink, but since I have the space overhead, I just fill it using the carafe. Most importantly, brews great coffee, and keeps it hot.'),
(1183, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-21', 'Toast all the things! I\'ve had this toaster oven for a year now & it has been working quite well. It\'s pretty easy to clean & has a lot of options to chose from for whatever you are cooking. It can get a bit hot on the top of it (which I guess is obvious), so probably avoid stacking anything plastic on top of this product. I\'m glad my boyfriend swayed me into getting a toaster oven compared to a toaster. Lazy person life saver!'),
(1184, 2, 1, 3, '2015-06-02', 'downsized from a six slice oven. This tiny one is too complicated. Dont recommend  it. Burning myself constantly. A lot of steps for a piece of toast!'),
(1185, 3, 1, 4, '2016-01-11', 'Great Product I would put 5 stars if the LCD display could withstand the highest temperature this oven can output. After 15 minutes it started to discolor and become unreadable, luckily it returned to normal after a couple of hours. I know this isn\'t what it is used for, but it shouldn\'t cook itself. Other than this, I haven\'t had a problem using this as my oven (my other two full sized ovens died) for the last 3 months. I would highly recommend it.'),
(1186, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-09', 'It works great. Hello Coffee maker with a purple flare to it.  When I purchased this I didn\'t think I would be taking it home from my current deployment, but I will ship it back.  I haven\'t had any issues with it, I do wish it would keep the size programmed from the last cup that I brewed but hey I can\'t really complain too much about that.  It works great.'),
(1187, 5, 1, 4, '2016-12-05', 'makes great coffee works well enough. the gold filter basket suggested is perfect. you need to be sure carafe is placed correctly- that the small dome on the carafe lid is pushing the basket\'s coffee valve up or you will have a mess. My purchased unit\'s face panel fell off. still worked, looked ugly, so i epoxied it back on. Probably got bashed in factory, packing or shipping. Othwise, - very good machine, superior to the Kr__s and the C__sinart, i owned, which were 3x more expensive. I set up the night before, hit the auto button and it\'s all ready in the morning. Safety shut-off after 2 hours.'),
(1188, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-09', 'This is the coffee pot you were looking for. So far it has been an excellent coffee pot. I love the removable water reservoir, swivel base and the push button filter release. This is the coffee pot to order and a great value. Buy it! Update: 07/15/2015 Still a great coffee pot. Easy to use and easy to clean.'),
(1189, 11, 1, 4, '2014-12-29', 'Works fine, wish it fit into under-cabinet bracket Much better than our 10-year old B&D toaster whose top elements stopes heating up. However, we had that toaster mounted under the cabinet and I wish his one fit in that bracket or had an under cabinet bracket to keep it off our limited counter space. I like the old fashioned \"ding sound\" it makes when your item is ready and the crumb try may make t easier to clean or not. We\'ll see in a couple months! It also has a \'stay on\' feature if you want to keep things warm, such as chicken nuggets or waffles.'),
(1190, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-25', 'Excellent We\'ve been using this for a while now and we love it. It is of high quality and works well. A bit pricey compared to other toasters, but worth the money.'),
(1191, 12, 1, 5, '2016-11-03', 'Perfect! Perfect for someone who may have a small kitchen or limited kitchen space.  Does the job of two appliances at half the space.'),
(1192, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-17', 'It toasts our bread nice in the morning Works well. It toasts our bread nice in the morning. The timer also worked for real. Ours, I mean, the one we previously owned doesn\'t work properly so we switched with this one. Keeps our morning toastin\'!'),
(1193, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-04', 'Works well, good price. It replaces a 20 year old Black and Decker that finally gave up the ghost. I use it mostly for toasting (mostly English muffins), since I use a microwave oven for warming things up and for some light duty cooking, and have a full scale electric range as well (which gets a LOT less use now than in the old days). Very happy that this B & D is still on the market, and at a reasonable price, and glad to have the light duty oven capability as a backup to the microwave.'),
(1194, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-25', 'Great coffee maker I love this coffee maker because the coffee is truly hot and water reservoir is removable and easy to clean. I would recommend it to others.'),
(1195, 3, 1, 2, '2016-07-09', 'Takes forever to toast. This is my third or fourth B&D toaster oven. It does what it is supposed to do but wow does it take a long time. My old toaster oven would toast a bagel in about three minutes. This takes - and I\'m serious, I times it - ten minutes! If you need a table top stove this will probably work for you, but as a toaster it sucks.'),
(1196, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-14', 'Five Stars Very satisfied with it.'),
(1197, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-08', 'It works great for its price A very simple, one-person coffeemaker. It works great for its price. It is fast and reliable. Unfortunately it has no auto-off function but I think it would be a little fancy for this price.'),
(1198, 9, 1, 5, '2015-07-04', 'my favorite coffee maker my favorite coffee maker'),
(1199, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-19', 'great This toaster oven is great. It is mostly black with stainless trim. It\'s looks pretty on the counter and has a whole lot of options on the knobs for heating. Comes with everything shown. The top, side and door do get very hot to the touch, so use with care.'),
(1200, 7, 3, 2, '2014-01-20', 'The basket broke the first week and will not stay up, pouring water all over the cabinet and risking a burn hazard. I am pitching it and buying a Hot Shot that will heat 16 oz at a time.'),
(1201, 11, 1, 3, '2014-06-15', 'Mostly Satisfied This toaster oven works good and looks good however, is difficult to get it to turn on. You have to turn the knob past a certain point a couple of times in order to get it to turn on. Once you get it to turn on it does a great job.'),
(1202, 3, 1, 4, '2016-09-27', 'Four Stars Good but wish more heavy duty.'),
(1203, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-14', 'Five Stars Great'),
(1204, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-01', 'Five Stars Nice product for the money paid.'),
(1205, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-30', 'Five Stars A great buy! Item just as described.  A gift. Simple and easy  to use. Thank toy'),
(1206, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-24', 'Five Stars Excellent coffee maker and better to not have a carafe!.'),
(1207, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-20', 'WOW Best coffee pot we\'ve ever had.  Love the no carafe idea but still makes a full pot.  We used an earlier model in a hotel room and this one is greatly improved with the removable water reservoir and removable coffee holder.'),
(1208, 5, 1, 2, '2015-09-23', 'Two Stars At times it seems really noisy when perking. If it continues, we\'ll call Hamilton Beach.'),
(1209, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'Five Stars easy to use.  price reasonable.'),
(1210, 4, 1, 2, '2016-01-24', 'Failed after three years. It worked well for the past three years, but it just lost it\'s ability to measure or regulate temp. Gets way too hot and burns bagels/toast. My only complaint, while it was working, was that the top and sides were very hit while being used. I would have given it 4 stars while it was working well, but failing after 4 years (a year after the 2 year warranty lapsed) is unacceptable.'),
(1211, 2, 1, 2, '2015-04-03', 'This one takes so long to make toast if you ... This one takes so long to make toast if you use rice breads.  I could make toast for the whole family by the time this one heats up. This does work okay with wheat breads, but takes longer than a regular toaster.'),
(1212, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-10', 'Five Stars Just what I needed. My 12 cup one was too big.'),
(1213, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-27', 'Bon voyage No power and small blades do not allow this to chop veggies and fruits well. I bought it to travel with and left it at my vacation rental; it was a waste of money unless all you\'re doing is blending yogurt and protein powder.  Nice weight and size though.'),
(1214, 7, 3, 5, '2016-07-29', 'I bought this for a gift for my daughter. The thing that attracted me to it was the fact that you could use the high priced K cups or you can just use actual loose coffee. My daughter uses it all the time! I like the fact she can have a little bit of something special just for her that doesn\'t cost her a lot of money. Her life is so busy with her kids and hubby and they are on a strict budget. She actually takes time now to make her a nice coffee. So glad she can have a little bit of a treat in her life that doesn\'t have any \"fluff\" in it! She said it works well too. Price was so much better than the expensive keurig ones. It actually made me look at other Hamilton Beach products since our experience with this one has been so positive!'),
(1215, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-15', 'Five Stars good stuff_ use it everyday'),
(1216, 6, 1, 3, '2016-05-23', 'Not a very good toaster Just ok. Takes a long time to toast anything and doesn\'t accommodate especially long or thick bread. Hope it wears out soon so I can justify buying a new one.'),
(1217, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-11', 'I was happy to see the model was still available I had one of these for 6 years and if finally gave out. I was happy to see the model was still available. It works great and the large size makes it easy to use for many items.'),
(1218, 6, 1, 4, '2016-07-18', 'Four Stars Great small toaster!.'),
(1219, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-30', 'Five Stars My favorite coffe maker ever!.'),
(1220, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-29', 'Five Stars suits us perfectly - simple, attractive, effective'),
(1221, 12, 1, 4, '2016-12-26', 'great product but shop and price watch this toaster oven went down in price as a day after i bought it.  great product but shop and price watch.'),
(1222, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-05', 'BEST COFFEE MAKER Ok hands down the best coffee maker I have owned and god knows - Ive owned a few.  The \"beep\" (yes there is one) is unobtrusive. It makes great coffee and keeps it hot.  The timer is easy to set.'),
(1223, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'Perfect small appliance! Love the toaster oven, perfect size for a family of two....I can\'t believe that this cost less them some toasters and you can cook in it...I made fish in it and it was awesome...will be making chicken legs tonight!'),
(1224, 3, 1, 3, '2015-08-06', 'just FINE! I have been using this for how many months now. I rate this as okay. It functions just fine but sometimes the buttons are not accurate especially when I cook meat. But not really a big problem to me, besides, it doesn\'t happen all the time.'),
(1225, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-08', 'Good Quality food the Price Nice toaster at a good price.  It does toast evenly as advertised.  the dials are a bit overly complicated to me.  But only I got the hang of them.  It is big enough for only a tiny 9 inch pizza.'),
(1226, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-10', 'We chose this product as a supplement to our K-cup coffee maker, the original, because was having minor problems with the old one. Never expected the Hamilton Beach coffee maker to actually replace our old one but we haven\'t used it since. This coffee maker has some great features. Choosing between 6, 8, or 10 ounce cup is simple with the integrated measuring reservoir. I think it\'s a good thing this maker does not have an internal water holding tank, using only the amount of water poured in for that particular cup being made at that moment. I believe any water holding reservoir type of brewer has the potential of mold. I refer to that type of brewing as replacement through displacement. This Hamilton Beach eliminates that possibility. It\'s fast too. By the time I get done adding creamer, sweetener, and a little evaporated milk to a freshly made cup, another cup is done brewing too. The choice of regular and bold brew is another feature we really like. Initially I thought maybe the difference between the two modes might be temperature but it turns out to be how the water is introduced into the K-cup or brewing basket with whatever your choice of ground coffee. The regular brewing mode continuously pushes the water through as with any K-cup brewer but what\'s different with bold mode is it will momentarily pause intermittently through most of the brew process. It really does make a difference too. My wife likes the regular brew mode and I like the bold mode. Wish we discovered this FlexBrew a long time ago.'),
(1227, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-01', 'great coffee maker makes great coffee and very hot and I love the idea of the water tank to the sink and fill good job the only thing it is slower than black 7decer'),
(1228, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-28', 'I received my Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffee Maker, 49997 as a Walmart Spark reviewer. I cleaned the new machine following directions in the enclosed booklet using 3/4 cup white vinegar to 3/4 cup water and ran 12 oz of clear water through the machine until it no longer had a vinegar smell. I used a K cup for my first cup. I filled the cup with water that I would be drinking my coffee from and poured the water from the cup into the reservoir. They ask that you do this so you do not overfill the reservoir. I would have preferred to have a reservoir on the side of the machine to fill with water and then select the size of the cup to fill from the machine. The Hamilton Beach FlexBrew makes a humming noise while it is brewing and a blue light is on for the entirety of the brewing cycle, which is not long. The coffee maker shuts off automatically when the brewing cycle is complete. When the lid is closed to brew a large hole is made in the K cup top by a pin in the lid and there is also a stab hole made at the bottom side of the K cup, which is made by a sharp blade in the cup dispenser where the K cup fits in. I am satisfied with my Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffee Maker.'),
(1229, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-24', 'good toaster - would buy again The white plastic out casing is a nice complement to my kitchen. I would buy it again. It was packaged well and arrived safely'),
(1230, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-08', 'Great Toaster Just received my CPT-142 white Cuisinart toaster.  I ran 2 slices of Cinnamon Raisin bread through and they came out perfectly the first time.  I\'ve toasted several more items and all were perfectly toasted on both sides with no striping whatsoever.  Very satisfied.'),
(1231, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-08', 'Great value fabulous value, better than toasters costing 4 times more.'),
(1232, 10, 1, 3, '2016-03-13', 'Good to carry around but isn\'t good at mixing Good to carry around but isn\'t good at mixing. I have to stir it with a spoon or shake it to make sure everything gets mixed.'),
(1233, 6, 1, 1, '2014-03-29', '50 Shades of Toast Even though I like my other Cuisinart products this one is pretty bad.  I returned it within 3 days because it toasts one side very dark and the other side is barely toasted at all.  There\'s only a couple things one needs in a toaster but toasting bread is at the top of that list and this one didn\'t measure up.'),
(1234, 4, 1, 5, '2016-04-21', 'Five Stars Love it! Great size and heats up super fast.'),
(1235, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-12', 'Five Stars I love this coffee machine..BEST EVER!'),
(1236, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-21', 'Great buy! This toaster has been great. It has different cooking settings (toast/broil/etc) and has a dial for time settings. It is easy to clean and the tray accessories is great for certain applications.'),
(1237, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-02', 'Wonderfully Designed This is one of the best designed coffee makers I have ever used.  The controls are easy to use, the coffee basket pops out for ease of use, the water reservoir is easy to access and separate from the coffee basket area, and it even has casters on the bottom so I can roll it easily on my countertop.'),
(1238, 5, 1, 3, '2015-03-17', 'Great except for cheap plastic lid. I\'ve had this for a week and loved it. I still love it, but I\'m sad because the lid to the carafe just broke. I removed it once with no problem (to go in dishwasher), but just now removing it for the second time, the plastic hinge just snapped right off. I am a small chick, I assure you it wasn\'t me handling it roughly. I must have just not done it just perfectly. For the plastic piece to break that easily that fast is really disappointing. I will probably look into a replacement carafe because I do love the machine. I wonder if this is under warranty...'),
(1239, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-07', 'Highly Satisfied w/ The New & Improved Keurig K240 2.0!!! I absolutely love the Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing System! This is very easy to set up than the older versions. It is very quiet when using. I love how it is touch screen. When I put a pod inside it automatically knows what I\'m brewing so it knows what size cup to fill. It also works with the K-Carafe pods as well. This system work way better and faster than my older Keurig K45 I had. The Keurig K45 was loud and so much slower than the Keurig K250 2.0. I also love how the K250 2.0 takes up less space than my old Keurig. Only thing is if you are a heavy Keurig user daily, then you may want to get one with a bigger water tank..but if you brew 4 pods or less a day, then this is a great option for you. Keurig has come a long way with their sleek designs and greatly improved brewing systems they offer today. I got this Keurig on an Amazon warehouse open box deal and was very impressed! I paid almost half the price and the Keurig was never used and still wrapped up in perfect condition with all items and manuals.'),
(1240, 5, 1, 3, '2015-09-07', 'Great coffee maker while it lasted Update Sept 2015: I contacted HB and they replaced the coffee maker and I only paid for shipping back ($12.99). I am still not too happy about the reliability of the unit but HB did respond to my complains and sent me another unit; hence updating to 3 stars. It died after six months, great coffee makes while it lasted. Really disappointing. I guess I have to go back to the cheap big discount store, don\'t waste your money on this one.'),
(1241, 8, 1, 4, '2016-03-29', 'Four Stars Nice'),
(1242, 6, 1, 5, '2014-04-16', 'Great little toaster LOVE this toaster :) Had a 4 slice one but needed something smaller, its hard to find a simple white toaster with all the luxury extras.  Actually bought a 2nd one for the kid when she heads off to school.'),
(1243, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-02', 'Five Stars Love the compact design. easy setup and use. Makes a great cup of coffee.'),
(1244, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-27', 'Hamilton Beach 51101BA Personal Blender My little portable traveling blender. It works perfectly fine. I love it.'),
(1245, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-24', 'very good brewer, coffee is very hot, I like this size very good for work or garage would recommend , and the shipping was very fast and right to the door with no hassle'),
(1246, 2, 1, 2, '2015-04-14', 'that\'s for sure and we\'ve always loved our B&D products Difficult to figure out- not very intuitive to use, that\'s for sure and we\'ve always loved our B&D products.'),
(1247, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-08', 'Finally one that works! Love it. Have had it over a month now and it was the best one so far. Wasn\'t a fan of the really bright clock but got used to it. Like that the water is at the back and don\'t have to worry about putting the coffee first and if it gets wet and messes up filter like I did with my Mr. Coffee. Really happy with it.'),
(1248, 6, 1, 3, '2015-12-06', 'An ok toaster that doesn\'t toast both sides of the bread the same I find it consistently toasts one side of the bread more than the other, regardless of which slot you use.'),
(1249, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-16', 'Best coffee maker we\'ve ever had We love this coffeemaker.  With our previous coffeemakers that had a carafe the water was always spilling when we poured the water in to the reservoir.  With this model you fill up the water tank at the sink and then just insert it into the unit.  Works great and love not having to clean the pot or worry about the glass carafe breaking.'),
(1250, 5, 1, 2, '2015-01-04', 'Two Stars Average for the most part.  No real issues except it quit after only 8 months of daily use.'),
(1251, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-31', 'Five Stars Very pleased with it.'),
(1252, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Love love love Love love love. Best thing about this is how fast the toaster takes to preheat. Like only 1-2 min for 350F.'),
(1253, 1, 1, 4, '2016-05-23', 'It seems like I\'m always filling the water reservoir It seems like I\'m always filling the water reservoir.  Another complain is that travel mugs won\'t fit underneath it.  Other than that, it\'s a Keurig and does what it should.'),
(1254, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Stop looking now! This is it! We are a very picky toaster oven family.  We use it excessively, so it needs to be just right.  Life of a toaster oven is about three to five years old here.  It takes us about three or four returns before we get the right one because new styles come out.  Well, this is the one! It toasts evenly.  Bakes and broils well.  Large enough for a small pizza, for real, but unit does not take up an enormous amount of space on the counter.  Tray comes out and cleans easily.  Only complaint is the fact that it does not have a timer for the oven setting, so it doesn\'t shut off, so you got watch it.  The bagel and toast settings shut off automatically at the desired darkness, which is the most important part, obviously.  Now, while typing this review, I just had the brilliant idea of buying a couple more, so we skip the testing out phase. Duh!  Dang lightbulb just flickers in this head at times.'),
(1255, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-07', 'Absolutely the best present I\'ve received in many years.  Heats up quickly,  works perfectly! Fabulous!.'),
(1256, 6, 1, 5, '2014-06-17', 'Love this toaster I use this everyday and it fits all sizes of bread from Eng. Muffins to sprouted breads. The cost was great too with free shipping.'),
(1257, 3, 1, 5, '2014-08-13', 'Solid machine I have only one word for it: the best of all I owed!'),
(1258, 10, 1, 3, '2016-01-02', 'Three Stars Great product however the blade amd the engine burned out too soon'),
(1259, 3, 1, 4, '2014-08-18', 'So far I love the oven but at this time cannot give it ... So far I love the oven but at this time cannot give it 5 stars as I haven\'t used the convection oven portion of it yet.  I have had a few Black & Decker items and have never had an issue with any of them.'),
(1260, 5, 1, 1, '2014-05-30', '2nd coffee maker dies within a year and HB SUPPORT IS CR@P Will keep it short as I am irate at this point and don\'t want to spoil your mood: When this coffee maker works its fine. However, we seriously doubt the quality controls at Hamilton Beach and more so, we detest their lack of customer centric support. The first one died within 6 months. First the timer stopped working. Then the power button stopped working. We didn\'t check the warranty and figured it was just bad luck and we went out and bought another via Amazon. 3 months later this one died. It simply wouldn\'t switch on anymore. This time we checked the warranty and figured we could call them to get a new one. Here is the trick with that: they make it really hard to get a new one. Kinda like insurance companies putting in fine print to ensure there is no payout. That, by itself, should be a deterrent for buying. They make you try and read the melted/ stamped bottom and that is sheer impossible. I could not read it to the rep and even sent a 13mp photo to them to read for themselves which they couldn\'t. When I finally offered to hold a current news paper next to it with a sign reading\" it\'s really me\" the rep gave in and asked me to take photo\'s of the plug cut from the cord and email it to them. HOWEVER, BEFORE THEY DID THAT THEY ASKED ME TO PAY 11$. That is where they go dirty: regardless of whether they send the item they keep the 11$. So if they then come back and say your photos are rejected, you are still SOL and need to file a creditcard claim which they will win due to the fine print stating you are paying them 11$ for the sheer awesomeness of getting their support on the phone. Anyhow, fast forward 2 weeks: no response anymore to any of the emails with the case number and the photos. They simply went on mute. Absolutely ridiculous, Hamilton Beeatch. Ipso Facto So here is what I recommend: it\'s a good coffee maker when it works but myluck was suspiciously short lived x 2. And when you need their client service, despite warranty, they will make it heart attack level tough to get that replacement. So DO NOT buy this online, but rather in a store that offers the 10 or 15$ 2 year no questions replacement. You will get the value out of that as this thing is possibly going to fail and you can avoid dealing with HB-BS. Good luck. We moved on to a Presto 02811 and due to its simplicity we love that, HB lost a customer and we don\'t care. Hope we warned you sufficiently as companies that treat customers like suspects in a line up and then hit the ignore button deserve no ones\' business. PS: yeah, I do dislike them this much, given their utter lack of customer care let alone service. It should be called the HB Customers we-don\'t-care plan.'),
(1261, 8, 1, 5, '2015-12-08', 'This one works great!! I highly recommend it I purchased this after returning the one with the stainless steel carafe. This one works great!!  I highly recommend it.'),
(1262, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-15', 'Broken bulb Product would have been find had it not arrived with a cracked bulb. It had already broken down all the boxes when I noticed the defect, so it wasn\'t worth the hassle of shipping it back and I just tossed it and will order another. Frustrating!'),
(1263, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-25', 'Five Stars love it.'),
(1264, 5, 1, 3, '2014-12-10', 'Long Brewing Time Brews a good cup of coffee, on the bold setting it is painfully slow.'),
(1265, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-29', 'Five Stars the best yet'),
(1266, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-07', 'Great price and gets the job done I bought this due to price, size and color.  I\'m keeping it and using it on my counter because it heats up quickly  unlike several other toaster ovens costing much more that I\'ve owned did not, easy to remove and clean crumb tray that slides right out, and reasonably efficient controls.  Easy to find the exact spot to set for the color toast I like. No, there\'s nothing automatic about this.  You really do have to check the dials and set them but is that really so hard?  Of course not.  The huge $125 one I was given several years ago lasted just two days on the counter.  It was way too big for my small space for it, took very long time to make a piece of toast, and just wasn\'t practical so was returned. For a toaster oven that will make cheese toast, breakfast toast, warm up and crisp a croissant  AND is relatively inexpensive, this is the one.'),
(1267, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-10', 'Fast delivery!!! Love the color!  It is great to just put your cup in place push the cup size and go!  No more putting water in before each cup.  Delivery of the Keurig was quicker than expected!'),
(1268, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Wonderful Coffee Maker I finally got my first Keurig and I absolutely love it! The convenience of this machine makes waking up at 5:30am enjoyable and easy. Plus there are so many great flavored Kcups to choose from. Definitely love this machine. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods with this review.'),
(1269, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-28', 'I\'m not one to give a bad review because I can usually find SOMETHING positive to ... I\'m not one to give a bad review because I can usually find SOMETHING positive to say about a product, but not this one.  From go it was a piece of junk.  It could not blend anything without constant stirring and then the juice would be chunky.  In less than 2 weeks it was dead.  The super dummer is that I bought 2 of them!  HUGE mistake.  Now, the second one goes to the second hand store so someone else can deal with it.  I bought a Ninja blender and am super stoked.  Don\'t waste you money on this blender unless you need a paper weight, and not a very good one at that.'),
(1270, 6, 1, 1, '2015-06-10', 'I decided to replace my 20 year old GE toaster ( still worked great ) with a new one with a crumb tray Probably one of the most disappointing purchases in my 61 years . I decided to replace my 20 year old GE toaster ( still worked great ) with a new one with a crumb tray . I purchased this toaster and am in total disbelief ...this thing is worthless. This is not rocket science , my dear Cuisinart , it\'s a frick\'n toaster ! Why is one side of my \"toast\" burnt at the bottom and barely toasted at the top....and the other side is even worse ? This thing will be gracing the local landfill soon and I will drive to Walmart and buy some cheap toaster that can actually make toast ! Geeez'),
(1271, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Keurig 2.0, Best Father\'s Day gift ever! I recently got my Keurig 2.0 for Father\'s Day and have enjoyed ridiculously good coffee ever since! Best Father\'s Day gift ever! Super easy to use, with so many choices it\'s really hard to pick your first K-Cup you want to brew. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(1272, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'This machine is great, especially the addition of the strong brew function This machine is great, especially the addition of the strong brew function. I only wish there was an option to brew a 12 oz. cup using the regular pods. Otherwise it heats the water fast, brews fast, and makes great coffee.'),
(1273, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-08', 'great toaster This toaster is amazing it has lasted almost 9 years now it makes perfect toast.'),
(1274, 10, 1, 3, '2015-07-22', 'This works good as long as I put all ingredients in and ... This works good as long as I put all ingredients in and let them sit for a while.  If I try using it as soon as I ad the frozen fruit or ice I have to use a spoon to mix it up during the process.'),
(1275, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-18', 'Hamilton Beach Coffee Maker, a good choice! I have had this coffee maker for awhile now and I love it. It is different from all the other makers because the water compartment is in the back and not poured out of the coffee pot into the maker. Make a decent pot of coffee too.'),
(1276, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-13', 'One Star awful... stuff sprays out of the lid.  absolute garbage'),
(1277, 10, 1, 3, '2015-06-01', 'Therefore I didn\'t operates it and it lay useless in my house in the meantime I received a blender that it operates at 115V line power. That is not suitable to my Country  power line 220V . Therefore I didn\'t operates it and it lay useless in my house in the meantime .'),
(1278, 2, 1, 3, '2016-04-25', 'Three Stars I find this product not to be user friendly.'),
(1279, 4, 1, 5, '2017-01-12', 'Five Stars Very happy with TOB-40N.'),
(1280, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-20', 'Great!!! Excellent machine....'),
(1281, 6, 1, 5, '2016-10-13', 'Five Stars Works great!.'),
(1282, 7, 3, 1, '2015-12-10', 'I have owned this unit for about a year...and that is all it is good for....it stopped working last week, would not heat the proper amount of water.....but, after 10 minutes, the rest of the water drains out! The garbage man is getting this one...'),
(1283, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-11', 'So far, the best toaster I\'ve ever had. Works great, toasts evenly.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1284, 4, 1, 3, '2015-05-30', 'Unfortunate Handy device that does all it is supposed to. Unfortunately the element melted and warped (bottom front). No replacement part is available. Absolutely ridiculous. Buying a Black and Decker one to replace this unit.'),
(1285, 11, 1, 3, '2014-10-01', 'Good as a toaster Slightly big for the counter.  Good as a toaster, but takes to long to bake pork chops and other meats'),
(1286, 6, 1, 2, '2015-05-23', 'I would have a great toasting machine I thought by ordering Cuisnart, I would have a great toasting machine.  So far, it either burns or does not toast enough.'),
(1287, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-31', 'Five Stars This is a high-end toaster, and I got what I expected.'),
(1288, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'Just what I needed! Just what I needed! This is a great toaster oven. very intuitive and easy to use.'),
(1289, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-13', 'I absolutely love this coffee maker I absolutely love this coffee maker. I don\'t understand the bad reviews. I love the fact that the water container is separate and can be removed to wash it. I love the blue lights because now I can set this one without having to use a flashlight. Makes great coffee. Nice and hot. In fact, I use to have to reheat the second cup after putting in my half and half, but now I don\'t. Would highly recommend this coffee maker.'),
(1290, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-15', 'Does the job and looks good doing it Toaster criteria: blend in design wise, fit in size wise, can\'t be crazy expensive, toast the bread, easy to clean. This toaster ticks all the boxes for us. Nice and compact, light weight, easy to keep clean, nice design without being showy (who needs a trophy toaster?). Turns out good toast. I\'m not a pixel peeper toast eater, so I can\'t say if this is the best most perfect ever toaster. But we like it a lot.'),
(1291, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-24', 'Five Stars Love it!.'),
(1292, 1, 1, 4, '2016-04-30', 'Great coffee but needs larger cup sizes! I am in love with my Keurig. I found a reusable Keurig cup at Walmart that allowed me to use coffee I already had. I have not spent $11+ on any coffee because of it. It\'s surprisingly fast at brewing and absolutely perfect for iced coffee. I am just disappointed that the largest size I can brew for is 10oz.'),
(1293, 4, 1, 2, '2015-07-06', 'I really liked the oven Have owned this oven for a little over 1 year.  Recently, the bottom front heating rod has warped/melted? And quit working.  You get a slight shock when you you touch the on/off button.  In reviewing the questions and answers above, it seems this is a frequent problem with this product. I called Cuisinart Customer Service since it is still under warranty. They charge you $10 shipping to get a replacement, and you are responsible for returning the defective unit at your cost. Not a very consumer friendly policy, especially since it is a known defect, and a serious safety issue to boot. Depending on the cheapest return shipping I can find, I may just send them  a $10 check and a picture of the warped heating element. Other than this problem, I really liked the oven.  I used it mainly for toasting and re-heating pizza.'),
(1294, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'Five Stars GREAT PRODUCT'),
(1295, 1, 1, 1, '2016-05-26', 'BEWARE!!!!  THESE PRODUCE MOLD!!!  READ BEWARE!!!!  I have one of these and they are quick to develop MOLD!  The top holder of the water container gets a lot of moisture that hangs on there.  IF you fill up the water canister and come back and look at it in a few hours you will see A LOT of moisture hanging from the top.  This moisture I noticed after a week began to MOLD UP.  I cleaned it and again a week later MOLD.  It\'s a manufacture defect in these machines.  I still have mine, but I only put enough water in it for 2-3 days and I no longer put the top on it.  At the end of the week I dump all the water out and allow it to completely dry.  If you own one of these and you start having health issues....CHECK the top, and even if you don\'t see the mold forming...CLEAN  IT, and now you\'ll need to clean the entire machine....and you\'ll be fine.  I\'m VERY surprised Keurig never noticed this.  I\'ll bet there is a class action suit on this before long.'),
(1296, 9, 1, 1, '2016-06-03', 'Leaks after short time. Bought the maker in January and less than 6 months later it leaks all over the counter.  The valve that leaks can not be reached for cleaning.  Previous Cuisinart maker valve was reachable and cleanable.'),
(1297, 2, 1, 3, '2015-06-08', 'Three Stars great price.'),
(1298, 9, 1, 4, '2016-01-24', 'I like it I\'ve had this coffee maker for about a month and I think it\'s great to not have to mess with a carafe. At first it didn\'t seem to get the coffee very hot, but it seems that with time it has gotten better.I had one incident with grounds getting into the seal and causing the spout to leak. The paper filter had gotten folded over by the water coming into the basket. I have since started using the permanent filter and have had no further problems with leaks.'),
(1299, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-01', 'Great drip coffee machine besides the noise Works fantastic, I love that I can choose to brew my coffee bold, and I LOVE that the coffee pot does not dribble when I pour it! I ignored the comment about the machine being loud, (thinking that most coffee machines make noise) and it is actually much louder than I expected at the end of the brew cycle. Noise aside, my coffee tastes great and is ready fast.'),
(1300, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-21', 'Yessss GIRL! It worked on my 4A Hair!! This product is shockingly and unbelievably amazing! I immediately took it out of the box 20 mins ago and plugged it in. I sectioned off a piece of my 4A hair. As soon as it was at 450*F, I took the brush through one time (yep, one time) and my hair straightened! It doesn\'t smell burned and it looks moisturized! Where has this been my entire life?!'),
(1301, 3, 1, 2, '2015-06-20', 'Terrible design After reading a lot of positive reviews, I decided to go with this oven. What a disappointment! If I had kept the box for it, I would have sent it back. Every time I use it, the outside, especially the top gets so hot that it will melt anything you might have left there, like the oven mitts that have rubber on the outside. The handles gets ridiculously hot as well, so I have to remember to use the mitts every one which I\'ve never had to do with other toaster ovens I\'ve had. The beeping sound is crazy loud as well. I only have it two stars because it actually cooks everything fine. I just have to remember not to touch it anywhere on the outside while it\'s on...'),
(1302, 11, 1, 4, '2014-11-15', 'Four Stars works great. we use it weekly. decent price. quick delivery. Cant beat it.'),
(1303, 4, 1, 5, '2016-08-09', 'This is a great little toaster oven This is a great little toaster oven. I have been using a 5 year old Black & Decker toaster oven (see photo of culprit soon to be in our local landfill).  This is one of the most dangerous fire hazards in my kitchen.  The timer sometimes does not shut off if one fails to turn the timer past the 10 minute mark and reset to anything below that.  I have had 4-5 fires start in this overn while I fortunately was standing by in the kitchen.  Worst design feature: the knobs cannot be turned without a cloth or other middleware to simply turn it.  One cannot turn the knobs with just fingers, really unbelievable that B&D let this be manufactured and sold under their name.  Wonder how many house fires have been started by this piece of design junk? A long about way to say, pay an extra 30 bucks and get a decent toaster oven by Cuisnart.'),
(1304, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-04', 'Nice addition to new kitchen I have only used this coffee maker a few times, replaced my old Krups. Easy to program, good tasting coffee, keeps it hot, the only thing I was disappointed in is the pot itself, it is plastic not glass, I think a glass pot is better for coffee brewing and holding.'),
(1305, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-03', 'I am very pleased. came as advertised and in a timely manner.  I am very pleased.'),
(1306, 5, 1, 2, '2015-12-02', '50-50 Odds That One Will Keep Working We bought 2 of these, my husband has his own (he likes his mud) and I like my coffee. Mine died last month. His is still working. Admittedly, I don\'t/didn\'t like that you have to be very careful when pouring that first cup or you end up with drips on the counter and the lid does not lock to the top of the carafe, but that wasn\'t a huge deal. The coffee stayed hot with no problem and there\'s a 2 hour timer. I ended up buying a different brand of coffee maker where I don\'t have to pick up a pot and can just stick my mug under the reservoir instead. I like it better. My husband is easier to please and he\'s ok with this one other than wishing it had a 4 hour timer. As short-lived as it was for me, I should give it 1 star, but I\'m trying to be overall fair on the basis of what works. It keeps the coffee hot for 2 hours, set your cup on a paper towel.'),
(1307, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-06', 'Good looks and nice personality The removable water reservoir is a hit. This is an upgrade from a Black and Decker which lasted over ten years but is now showing its age. We are holding it in reserve.  We also have a French press and an espresso maker.'),
(1308, 6, 1, 3, '2015-02-19', 'Excellect product EXCEPT for uneven toasting i love this product EXCEPT as most reviews state, it toasts unevenly--one side much darker then the other (with or without pressing the bagel setting).  I will keep it because I don\'t mind that--but if it bothers you to have one side of toast come out almost crisp while the other side is lightly toasted, buy something else.  I can\'t honestly give this more than three stars though. Sorry.'),
(1309, 6, 1, 4, '2015-04-07', 'Four Stars It\'s nice...My wife loved it...'),
(1310, 6, 1, 3, '2015-03-30', 'Just OK - Bagel Setting doesn\'t work We\'ve had this toaster for about a year now and I guess OK would be the most accurate rating.  Day to day toasting works pretty good and for the most part it\'s reasonably consistent. Our main dissatisfaction is with the bagel setting, it simply doesn\'t work.  no matter how you try it the bottom of the bagel gets overdone and hard as a rock while the top toasts fine.  For someone who eats a lot of bagels this is a big issue.  For a fairly expensive \"top of the line\" toaster it\'s disappointing.'),
(1311, 4, 1, 1, '2015-01-27', 'If you  want golden toast...DON\'T ORDER THIS ITEM!! Very disappointed.  \"Toast\" setting leaves butter side virtually untoasted and bottom side over cooked!  Offensive odor of burnt toast fills the house!'),
(1312, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-31', 'Five Stars Bread is a toastin like it did in 1986!'),
(1313, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Five Stars Works as we hoped it would.'),
(1314, 1, 1, 5, '2016-07-02', 'Five Stars GOOD.. I MIGHT HAVE TO GET A BIGGER ONE.'),
(1315, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-01', 'Love it This is my 3rd one, I love it but my wife likes to break the carafe in our stone sink. Hard to find a replacement and if you so they are almost as expensive as buying a new coffee maker.'),
(1316, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'I use this every morning to blend frozen fruit smoothie and with a couple of smacks it works fine. For the price you can\'t beat it.  Yes its cheap and you sometimes have to shake it around to get it to blend all the way, but for less than 15 bucks what do you expect?  I use this every morning to blend frozen fruit smoothie and with a couple of smacks it works fine.'),
(1317, 4, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', 'Receiving party was overjoyed and has been using constantly since Given as a replacement gift for a toaster oven (different brand) that quit. Receiving party was overjoyed and has been using constantly since.'),
(1318, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-24', 'Five Stars enjoy all features'),
(1319, 4, 1, 5, '2016-11-21', 'Five Stars Works very well.'),
(1320, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-05', 'Five Stars Awesome toaster and great price'),
(1321, 2, 1, 2, '2015-10-03', 'BLACK & DECKER COULD HAVE DONE A BETTER DESIGN JOB 1) The cord is too short.  2)The control knobs are a pain in the . . . to adjust.'),
(1322, 5, 1, 1, '2016-10-06', 'Great coffee maker if your okay with a 3 month lifespan Loved the design. Wanted removable water tank so cleaning would be easy, liked the timer as well and it made good coffee. Problem is the coffee maker only lasted 3-4 months. Can\'t return as Hamilton Beach won\'t warranty items purchased outside their website. Farewell Hamilton Beach.'),
(1323, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-14', 'Digital is better than dials The precision that a digital toaster oven provides is well worth the additional money. The dial version is considerably less expensive but the results from cooking/toasting vary widely.'),
(1324, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-01', 'Five Stars Works Great !.'),
(1325, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-07', 'Five Stars Excelente'),
(1326, 9, 1, 1, '2015-11-23', 'One Star Leaks and overflows like crazy and P-Poor customer service from Cuisinart!!!  Don\'t buy it!!!'),
(1327, 9, 1, 1, '2016-12-28', 'Just a warning I will start by saying something nice... It is nice looking.  Other than that I was very disappointed by the quality of the coffee it brewed and it\'s strange design. At first I was confused and appalled at the horrible burnt coffee smell that permeated my kitchen and home only to discover that the inner \'holding carafe\' that was removable, had an inner metal heating pad to keep the brewed coffee \'hot\' seemed to burn the coffee into a weird and strange tast and smell.  All I can say is \"buyer beware\".  I\'ve never experienced a coffee maker to make horrible tasting coffee before and I want to warn others before they try it themselves.  I have ditched it and bought a new one since then and was very relieved to have a \'normal\' tasting cup of coffee after I did so.  Sorry, I\'m just being honest.'),
(1328, 11, 1, 5, '2016-01-24', 'Best Simple Little Toaster Oven Dinner for one was perfect thanks to this toaster.  So sleek and light and easy to use!  I had to give this to my friend because her toaster caught on fire and I was moving, but she loves it just as much as I do!  Fits waffles, bagels, toast, bagel bites, leftover pizza, all the good stuff!'),
(1329, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-26', 'Cuisinart Toaster is A1 My mom loves this Toaster and transaction was flawless!!.'),
(1330, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-17', 'Five Stars Works very well, just a bit too small for most of my baking dishes.'),
(1331, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'Five Stars Works fine. No issues with it yet'),
(1332, 3, 1, 3, '2016-05-15', 'Three Stars Comes with only one slotted tray to hold baking sheets although it can hold 2.'),
(1333, 2, 1, 2, '2016-04-27', 'easy bake oven it\'s really small. like really small. i should have known better. it\'s like a toy oven.'),
(1334, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-24', 'Great Value! Came quickly, works great and small compact size!  I have a small city apartment and counter space is limited.  It is small enough to stash away when not in use.'),
(1335, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-16', 'User Friendly to the max I just wish I had looked at the reviews on Amazon before I purchased the Mr. XXXXX lemon (#ECX41CP). I bought this Hamilton Beach coffeemaker to replace a new Mr. XXXXXX machine that I had recently purchased from Costco which I returned to Costco. It was a nightmare and not user-friendly at all. Anyway, this machine is about as user-friendly as it gets. The removable reservoir is great, but I prefer to pour the water into it from the carafe which is also easy and does not get water all over my counter like the Mr. XXXXX did. The swing-out basket makes it easy to remove the basket and replace it after filling with coffee. Bonus is that it makes great coffee too! Thank you to the engineers at Hamilton Beach for a great coffeemaker.'),
(1336, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-24', 'It does the job Replacing an old 4 slice toaster that always got the bread stuck. This does the job. Not real impressed with the timer. You have to watch your toast close. But that\'s ok. It toasts evenly. Warm setting turns on the broiler unit not the bottom unit. Will just use bake setting from now on to warm bread. But overall happy with it. Does not take up much more room than the old toaster.'),
(1337, 6, 1, 2, '2015-08-18', 'This can\'t be a Cuisinart!!! This is not Cuisinart quality.  What a hoot.  One side of toast is perfect and the other is barely toasted.  Hope the pictures show the \"quality\" of the product.'),
(1338, 11, 1, 4, '2014-12-03', 'Buy it- you won\'t find anything cheaper. Bargain for the price. Works well'),
(1339, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-22', 'Five Stars Great'),
(1340, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-27', 'Five Stars Toasts great. the same every time. A great buy.'),
(1341, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-21', 'Five Stars Awesome working coffee maker.  Functionality is wonderful as removing the water reservoir is a convenient feature.'),
(1342, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-17', 'Toaster oven/ toaster This is great. I really love it. You can toast things or heat things upon the toaster oven.'),
(1343, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-01', 'Toaster Oven Nice oven but hard to see dial settings.'),
(1344, 6, 1, 2, '2016-08-02', 'Very disappointed - uneven toasting I purchased the toaster because of the positive reviews. Very disappointed - uneven toasting, and completely unreliable settings. Stay away from this lemon.'),
(1345, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-18', '... oven that died on me after 6 years of good use. I am happy about this oven except ... This was a replacement for a toaster oven that died on me after 6 years of good use.  I am happy about this oven except the fact that it is much smaller than expected.  The controls can be a bit tricky until you get familiar with the settings.  I made biscuits and they turned out perfectly with the baking setting.  Just wish I could get more on the little baking dish ,but for the price, it is definitely worth it.  Would give it 5 stars if it was a little more oven space.'),
(1346, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-10', 'Five Stars Makes great coffee'),
(1347, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-30', 'Five Stars works well.'),
(1348, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-05', 'I am very satisfied with it ! I was looking for a nice size oven I found this one Works very good 1st day I made cake. On the 2nd day I made lasagna it is a very good oven so far I am very satisfied with it.'),
(1349, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-16', 'Four Stars Works fine, still learning how to use the different levels.'),
(1350, 9, 1, 4, '2016-01-18', 'Four Stars We like this machine a lot. But wish the coffee stayed warmer longer'),
(1351, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-18', 'A Toast to Cuisinart This is a great little toaster! Inexpensive, solid and gets the job done well--I love that I can \"cancel\" toasting instead of having to wait for it to pop up or forcing it to pop up. Great buy!'),
(1352, 5, 1, 4, '2015-06-17', 'Four Stars I like this coffee maker it is very convenient .'),
(1353, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-16', 'Five Stars Works great!'),
(1354, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Very satisfied with this Keurig!! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.  I have purchased other pod making coffee machines prior to owning this one and this machine is excellent.  It brews very fast and the size options are great.  This model also is a good size for a kitchen counter and was not as wide as previous Keurig machines I\'ve seen.  The flavor of the coffee also seemed to be very smooth and flavorful when using this brewer over other brands I\'ve used.  I like the fact too that this unit allows you make the coffee stronger with the option to push the display with a finger when it appears.  I also like that it tells you when to add water so you don\'t have to guess if it needs water.  I would not hesitate to buy this model and recommend it highly!'),
(1355, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-02', 'Five Stars Excellent value'),
(1356, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-29', 'Okay, but too small for baking Very small toaster over, but it does a lot. You can\'t fit a bowl in there, so I would rather buy a bigger one for making small cakes in soup bowls. Or say a small loaf of bread. Works well and does what it says.'),
(1357, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-10', 'Perfect size - I\'m the only coffee drinker in the ... Perfect size - I\'m the only coffee drinker in the house. Also a good size when I have company since I can make a couple of cups at a time.'),
(1358, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Five Stars Works good.'),
(1359, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Awesome! Great product and such a funky colour!!'),
(1360, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-30', 'Five Stars Makes great toast quickly and looks nice on the counter.'),
(1361, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-23', 'Don\'t buy! Motor burned out after only a few uses.'),
(1362, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-24', 'Five Stars This toster works a lot better than a mikecrawave.It is nice to have in your kichon.A+++++'),
(1363, 12, 1, 4, '2016-07-09', 'Hamilton Beach makes good and compact toaster ovens - in our experience We purchased this product at a local retailer and they discontinued it. We have used (other brands) toaster ovens on the market that do not heat up the foods as fast as this unit does. Pros: This unit is small and does not take up a lot of counter space. We own two of them. Hamilton Beach makes good and compact toaster ovens - in our experience. The food is toaster pretty fast. I dont\' have to worry about having to use the microwave for foods that require toasting/broiling. My toasts are done fairly quickly in the morning. Compact - we spent some time looking for a compact unit. Most manufacturers are making very large units. Cons: I would have given it a five if it provided an auto-shutoff or alarm. If you forget the toasts, they will burn but that is the case with most toaster ovens.'),
(1364, 11, 1, 5, '2014-12-14', 'Great price. Fast delivery Item as described. Great price. Fast delivery. Will use seller again.'),
(1365, 4, 1, 5, '2015-09-03', 'Five Stars LOVE IT'),
(1366, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-02', 'Five Stars If it only have a timer.....'),
(1367, 5, 1, 2, '2016-07-18', 'Two Stars Front top cover (over the buttons) broke on day two of using this.'),
(1368, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-12', 'In almost 40 years of making a home, I\'ve ... In almost 40 years of making a home, I\'ve been through multiple coffee makers and they all let me down for one reason or another. If someone were to custom make one for me, it would have the exact features found here. It has the auto-brew feature that I require, so I can put my coffee together at bedtime and I wake to aroma of it brewing. Of course it has the 2-hour auto shutoff for my safety. No problem to just hit the button if there is still coffee left that I want to keep warm. It has the \"cheat\" feature I require some mornings, also known as pause-and-brew, that lets you sneak out a cup without coffee running everywhere.'),
(1369, 1, 1, 1, '2016-05-27', 'This is an easy action but still requires 5 minutes These 2.0 machines (I have 2 for different houses) are so unreliable.  Why do I use the K-cups - so I can grab a cup on the way out the door or offer variety to guests.  Regularly both machines will not dispense coffee until I clean the needles with a paperclip.  This is an easy action but still requires 5 minutes. This is infuriating.  It is almost as quick to boil water in the microwave and use a press for a better cup of coffee.  Boo to Keurig for this machine.  I dropped and cracked the reservoir on my B70 but I just ordered a new reservoir and will donate this to the kids garage sale.'),
(1370, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-05', 'Five Stars Good quality'),
(1371, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', 'Excellent coffee maker Excellent coffee maker. I waited just about 3 months to write this review. I wanted to make sure it works great over time. No complaints. No leaks. Easy to use. Temperature is consistent. It brews excellent coffee whether you make less than 4 cups or a whole pot. I really like the lever feature and the 1-4 cup brew feature. What\'s nice is that if you let the coffee sit, it does not taste burned. It\'s also easy to clean. I use it everyday.'),
(1372, 4, 1, 1, '2016-03-16', 'Disappointed. Very poor quality. Had to return it after a few days.  Expected better from this brand.'),
(1373, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-22', 'I absolutely love this little machine I absolutely love this little machine. My husband and I are coffee lovers and this little guy is perfect for our coffee station when we don\'t have enough time to use the french press. With literally just one button, no hassle, and no bulk - I\'m in love. I\'ve had enough stressful multi function bulky machines that die on me after a year and cost 5 times the amount. Thanks Black & Decker!'),
(1374, 3, 1, 4, '2014-12-28', 'very versatile! Really like this oven a lot....my only \"wished for improvement\" would be a door that has a \"stop\" and doesn\'t crash to the countertop if you let go of it!'),
(1375, 10, 1, 2, '2016-03-12', 'I thought this was an amazing product for the price you pay I bought mine right before Christmas in 2015 and it only lasted two months with daily use of making my ice-blended protein drinks.  The gear on the one and only cup you get came loose and would not spin on the blender motor gear. Before the product failure, I thought this was an amazing product for the price you pay.  It was fairly quietly and you could pulse a few times to get the consistentcy to your individual taste.  The cup was large and didn\'t overfill or leak.  However, I think that a product should last longer than two months.'),
(1376, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-29', 'Great toaster-Oven I bought a good sized convection oven (it will cook two 12\" pizzas) and I thought I didn\'t need the toaster-oven I\'ve had for six years and was still perfectly good, so I gave it away. I didn\'t have room for both of them anyway. Well, I was wrong. The convection oven is great for cooking almost anything I can do in my big oven, and without adding to the heat in the house on those 110 degree Texas days, but not worth a damn for toast. And since I like my morning bagels & cream cheese, and garlic toast with my pasta, I had to buy this replacement, same size, same brand, same price. Only now it sits on TOP of my convection oven.'),
(1377, 12, 1, 5, '2015-11-01', 'Five Stars Works great great value'),
(1378, 5, 1, 1, '2014-12-04', 'The machine worked fine for about 8 months until we noticed that it ... We bought this cofeemaker to replace an old Cuisinart machine. The machine worked fine for about 8 months until we noticed that it would start dripping if the carafe was removed during the coffee brewing process. It only got worse after few months despite carefully cleaning the valve. Just recently the front panel covering the digital elements came off probably as a result of the vapor heat. I was a able to reach Hamilton Beach and the unit will be replaced. I will be buying a different brand and give away the replacement unit when I get it.'),
(1379, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-03', 'Five Stars Much more quiet than my old Keurig.'),
(1380, 9, 1, 2, '2015-02-16', 'Makes great coffee and even has a tiny led so you ... Makes great coffee and even has a tiny led so you can fill in the dark, but reservoir indicator stops working at half. Cuisinart wants me to send it back for a replacement. For what I paid, I think they should send me a replacement in a box with a return shipping label! Do that and I will rate at 5 stars.'),
(1381, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-20', 'My machine works great. Always there for my morning cup of coffee ... My machine works great. Always there for my morning cup of coffee in the morning. Sometimes the screen looks weird, but if you unplug it, and plug it back it back in, it always seems to fix it. Love it!'),
(1382, 7, 3, 2, '2014-03-20', 'You have to follow the instructions before you use it the 1st time. After that its easy to use. However its has too many flaws to recommend it. Its hard to insert K Cups or reusable K Cups in the place meant for them. The spot where you put water in is bad. Its hard to put water in there without spilling some water on the counter. You have the option to use ground coffee but that option doesn\'t work. Every time I use that the coffee spills everywhere. One time I even used a K Cup and all the stupid thing did was make noise and spill the coffee. It does work okay most of the time but for every 10th time used it acts up. I use a real, true, Keurig at work and its better all the way around. Its easier to use, makes the coffee better, and doesn\'t spill at all. So to sum it up just avoid this coffee maker. You are much better off paying $100 which is double the price for a real, true, Keurig, that will work every time and last years.'),
(1383, 3, 1, 1, '2016-08-18', 'Disappointed I gave this as a wedding gift (bought in advance) and unfortunately, is now outside of the return period. It takes 30-40 mins to just heat up to 350 and the broiler doesn\'t work at all. Very disappointed!.'),
(1384, 8, 1, 5, '2015-07-03', 'Five Stars Great!'),
(1385, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-18', 'Love It Bought this for my sister-in-law.  She loves it!  What a great product and price. >^..^<.'),
(1386, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-09', 'Best Coffee Maker By far the best coffee maker I\'ve had. The reservoir works perfectly with no leaks. So convenient.'),
(1387, 7, 3, 1, '2016-10-08', 'it leaked from bottom and coffee would not brew into cup'),
(1388, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'Five Stars perfect toaster oven!  fits great under counter and looks nice.  toast great too!'),
(1389, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-24', 'Using it for two months now and love it. I especially like the 2 hour shut ... Using it for two months now and love it. I especially like the 2 hour shut off. No more worries about leaving the pot on!'),
(1390, 6, 1, 4, '2015-09-11', 'Four Stars Top is not insulated, gets too hot.'),
(1391, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-12', 'Five Stars Very nice and works great.'),
(1392, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-12', 'Best Coffeemaker for the price I have to say we had a Mr Coffee Coffeemaker in our office and the pot constantly leaked when you poured a cup.  We bought this and this is seriously the best bargain coffeemaker.  The coffee is hot, brews quick and the pot does not leak when you pour a cup.'),
(1393, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'We\'ve had it a couple months now and love it. The auto-program works great as well as ... This replaced our second Cuisinart.  The warmer on the first one quit working and the auto-program and warmer quit working on the second one.  I decided to try a different brand and settled on this one based on other reviews.  We\'ve had it a couple months now and love it.  The auto-program works great as well as the warmer that keeps the coffee hot.  The only thing is that there is a lot of steam that comes out the top during the coffee making process so I move it out from under the cabinet until it\'s ready.  I don\'t want that much moisture on the undercabinet light or wood.'),
(1394, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-02', 'Five Stars Good product, good price.  Works as well or better than much higher priced products.'),
(1395, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-09', 'Motor not strong enough for thick smoothie. I bought ... Motor not strong enough for thick smoothie. I bought two and both motors burnt out. And when you add ice you can smell motor. Okay for thin liquid smoothie.'),
(1396, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'I Love My New Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing System Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.  I\'ve recently upgraded to this brewer from my original Keurig k-cup brewer and I am very pleased that we did so. This brewer has touchscreen controls and also has the capability to brew a carafe of Keurig coffee as well as just a single cup. It really comes in handy when the neighbors get together every Saturday morning that we can brew 5-6 cups at time rather than individual servings. Thank you Keurig for taking coffee lovers into the next generation.'),
(1397, 4, 1, 5, '2016-08-09', 'Five Stars excellent product.'),
(1398, 5, 1, 3, '2016-03-05', 'Three Stars Top button grill is falling apart already!!  only a week old!  Makes coffee ok.. Just kinda bummed..'),
(1399, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-12', 'Easy to use plus makes great coffee! Works great: pours without a wayward drip, detachable water bucket, slid-out detachable coffee filter holder,... oh yeah: makes great tasting coffee! Priced right, easy to use... what more could you ask for in an automatic coffee maker?!'),
(1400, 8, 1, 5, '2014-12-02', 'Five Stars this coffee maker makes great coffee'),
(1401, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-27', '... was a replacement for an older model that I loved. It is terrible This was a replacement for an older model that I loved. It is terrible. I have had cups of cold coffee, cups full of grounds, cups with barely an inch of coffee, reheating cycle randomly coming on, wasted so many expensive pods as of course now I am forced to buy Keurig sealed ones. Customer service is no help. I don\'t have the box but am going to try and return to the store and buy a different brand.'),
(1402, 10, 1, 4, '2015-05-10', 'Good but too small Good, but too small, it comes with only 1 cup. It works for shakes only, or 1 cup frozen, thinks like that. For 10 bucks more you can get a full size blender. I\'ve returned it'),
(1403, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Great for students I thought it would be a good idea to get myself a Keurig machine before school started back up, and I\'m glad I did! The Keurig is wonderful, compact, and it makes coffee super fast, even though the preheating can be a little loud sometimes. So far I\'ve been enjoying the flavor of all the drinks I\'ve tried. The only downside is that the machine doesn\'t work with off-brand K-cups. But I would recommend this line to all those thinking of investing in a Keurig. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1404, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-29', 'Good basic toaster oven. Excellent basic toaster oven. Replaced the same model about 12 years old. Liked the old one, like this one too.'),
(1405, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-31', 'Definitely worth every penny! Absolutely love this toaster oven!! It\'s definitely a steal for the price, very well made and super chic looking'),
(1406, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'Great, simple toaster at a fair price. Great, simple toaster! My wife loves the pullout crumb tray. Works great in all modes.'),
(1407, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-07', 'Hard turning controls The oven has worked well for us. Our only complaint is the stiffness of the dials. My 87 year old mom cannot turn the bottom control because it turns so hard.'),
(1408, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'Five Stars Great toaster oven, awesome buy at the price.'),
(1409, 6, 1, 4, '2016-03-13', 'nice I am very glad that i purchased this awesome item at this price'),
(1410, 7, 3, 5, '2014-03-31', 'This pot is really versatile as it uses the K cups,can use for the pods, and can brew with ground coffee as well. You can use it for tea or chocolate too.'),
(1411, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-13', 'Most Perfect Coffee Maker in History!!! I love this coffee maker so much!  It looks so sleek and elegant in the kitchen.  I especially like that it tells you the time in bright blue numbers.  I actually like pouring the water in the hidden plastic container in the back rather than in the pot first and then at the top second.  It\'s not noisy at all and it\'s very easy to clean.  I really like the little roller wheels it has so that you can easily move it over if need be.  What I find really interesting is that it stays perfectly in place wherever you leave it even with the wheels.  I had imagined it rolling all over the counter and yet at the same time it\'s super easy to move over if necessary.  I also love the little button it has that pops out the filter cup.  This model truly is perfect!!!  It also came beautifully packaged.'),
(1412, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'A++++ I love my keurig! This is the only way I drink coffee now! It\'s my favorite! I encourage everyone to go buy one!! Thanks keurig, for the free pods for writing this review!'),
(1413, 6, 1, 1, '2015-03-20', 'One Star Burns the toast every time.'),
(1414, 12, 1, 3, '2015-06-01', 'Not bad I wish it had a bagel setting'),
(1415, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-29', 'Four Stars Works fine, the various heat levels and times are overly complicated and honestly detract from the otherwise sleek appearance'),
(1416, 2, 1, 2, '2015-02-09', 'If your vision isn\'t perfect you will hate it I am giving this toaster oven two stars based on one highly annoying and completely unnecessary  feature.  The design team did not only neglect to make the control settings readable. It seems they went out of their way to assure they were difficult to see.  Even the illustration of the controls on the quick start guide, copied at twice the original size, is hard to see. The photo for this item shows a good looking minimal style with the three big nobs and it just looked user friendly but that is an illusion.  Yes, its a nice size and is attractive but instead of enjoying my new oven I am angrily cursing it as I fetch a magnifying glass for every use.  Thanks a bunch Black and Decker.  Update - I was contacted by the company that manufactors these ovens for B and D and a bigger oven with easier to read (and turn) controls.was offered to me.  I agreed and am pleased.  TO1216B is the replacement so I\'ll go review that now.'),
(1417, 8, 1, 5, '2014-08-07', 'This little pot has worked beautifully and we find that we are using it now ... We wanted an inexpensive, fast brewing pot for those times we were out of Keurig pods. This little pot has worked beautifully and we find that we are using it now almost more than our Keurig, mostly because of the cost of the pods and we do drink a lot of coffee. For those who really want taste, quality and aren\'t concerned about price - go for the Keurig. For those concerned about price and prefer quantity to taste, buy this little pot!!'),
(1418, 8, 1, 2, '2015-03-17', 'Not recommended if you care about the quality of your coffee. I\'ve had this coffee maker a couple weeks now - my trusty old Tatung finally broke down after 9 years. I honestly didn\'t think the brand made that much difference - it\'s just a coffee maker right? With the Black and Decker the coffee has been generally weaker and less flavorful, which I initially thought was just a difference between the cone-shape and basket-shaped filters (this one is basket). However, today i opened up the top after brewing and saw that there was a big clump of dry grounds above all the moistened grounds. This means that a significant portion of the grounds aren\'t even being used when it brews. No wonder its so weak. Boo. Maybe I\'ll try pour-over next.'),
(1419, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'I absolutely LOVE my new Keurig!!! I love my new Keurig. I had one of the older models for about 2 years now and boy do I wish I would have upgraded sooner. It makes the perfect cup of coffee (up to 10 oz. might I add) every time! The digital display is more interactive which lets me know what going on. Not to mention, it\'s very quick and efficient. I can\'t wait to buy the Carafe. You won\'t regret this purchase. I promise!!!!! I received this product free for testing purposes.'),
(1420, 12, 1, 2, '2016-02-26', 'Buy a separate toaster and toaster oven No timer and the plates that were included don\'t fit.'),
(1421, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-02', 'Really nice coffee maker. I got this coffee maker to replace an old one that cost twice the price, and this one works better! I hated that my old machine didn\'t make my coffee that hot and didn\'t stay hot for long. This one gets the coffee really hot (and you can change the temp) and keeps it that way! Perfect for me.'),
(1422, 7, 3, 2, '2015-01-08', 'The thing \"worked,\" but nothing close to Keurig. First, it is very annoying and difficult to pour water into the brewer. It always spills. Second, it takes a LONG time to heat up and then brew (5-7 minutes?). I honestly was able to start (measure/add water, scoop/add coffee) an entire 12 cup pot of coffee in my old traditional brewer in the time it took for this to brew. It also is messy and tends to always drip a decent amount of coffee even after you think it is done. I returned this and just got a Keurig. The Keurig at least has a much better and larger water reservoir and it will get your coffee brewed in about 1 minute. This just wasnt worth the money saved in my opinion. I think a $15 traditional coffee pot is better than this one, and the coffee is much cheaper.'),
(1423, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', 'Great Little Blender Great little blender, great travel blender. I travel for work every week and fits in travel bag or suitcase perfectly.'),
(1424, 3, 1, 5, '2014-09-28', 'I am so glad that B&D has not discontinued this style because it ... We had an older version of this oven, and have had it for almost 10 years.  The only reason we are now replacing it is because the timer is stuck in position and it will not allow the oven to function except for toast.  Personally, I think it was something that we may have accidentally done ourselves and not an issue with the oven. I have never had a toaster oven last anywhere nearly that long.  I am so glad that B&D has not discontinued this style because it is by far the finest unit on the market.  We cook comolete meals for 5 in this oven!! We just received this oven and it is even better than our last one!!  Thank you B&D!!'),
(1425, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-14', 'Everything done right very well designed-easy to use, including the carafe from which you can pour coffee without losing any'),
(1426, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-04', 'Five Stars I use this daily for my protein shakes. Ice and fruits blend well.'),
(1427, 5, 1, 3, '2016-01-17', 'It makes good coffee, but the water temp isn\'t very hot ... Adequate. I have finally figured out that there\'s no such thing as the \"perfect coffee maker\". It makes good coffee, but the water temp isn\'t very hot right after brewing. You have to set the warming plate to the highest temp, and let it sit for a few minutes. Like most coffee makers these days, it has an auto-shutoff after two hours, which I personally dislike. Sometimes, like on the weekends, you\'d like to keep a pot going for a little longer than that. The LCD display is very bright, too, and could have a dimmer setting. All in all, worth the price.'),
(1428, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-28', 'Five Stars Vera good'),
(1429, 7, 3, 5, '2015-12-09', 'The Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single Serve Coffee Maker in red looks great in my kitchen and works perfectly for me as I\'m single and never drink enough coffee to make brewing even a 4 cup pot of coffee worth the waste. I love that it brews a cup or a travel mug of coffee, hot cocoa, tea, etc., quickly and is ready to brew another for the times I have company.'),
(1430, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-27', 'Great value Great value - wish the machine took the cone shaped filters.'),
(1431, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-04', 'Recommended. I read the reviews and I am very pleased with this unit. The gauge works fine for me. Maybe the negative posts prompted the manufacturer to update the gauge? I would recommend this coffee maker to anyone. Easy to set up, use, and clean. All the parts remove for easy cleaning and the LED light is a nice touch when filling the cup. Larger cups don\'t seem to be an issue either as the clearance is over 6 inches without the catch tray. If you\'re considering this coffee maker, it will not disappoint.'),
(1432, 7, 3, 1, '2016-03-30', 'This machine only worked for 1 day. I ended up getting 3 cups of coffee for $49.00. Terrible, spend a little more and get a better machine.'),
(1433, 6, 1, 5, '2014-05-30', 'Toaster I love it. It works very well, so far.  I like it\'s design and it\'s look. It was not overly expensive, well worth the cost.'),
(1434, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Five Stars Works perfectly. Cooked brisket in it!'),
(1435, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-31', 'Five Stars This toaster is very high quality.'),
(1436, 3, 1, 4, '2015-07-10', 'I am happy with the oven itself I am happy with the oven itself. However, do not click on the \"Frequently Bought Together\" link as those items will not fit inside this compact oven!'),
(1437, 9, 1, 1, '2015-12-17', 'looks nice outside but the reservoir that supposed to keep the ... looks nice outside but the reservoir that supposed to keep the coffee hot is plastic and coffee is warm. You better off with a glass pot that will keep coffee hot.'),
(1438, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-13', 'Don\'t want no short, short cords. This toaster works fine, but this short-ass cord bullcrap.  No, really.  It\'s just over a foot, which ensures that I need an extension cord if I want to place the toaster at a convenient location for me.'),
(1439, 2, 1, 1, '2016-03-27', 'Knob broke within 14 days oven temperature knob has already broken.  The knob is 100% plastic and has no metal sleeve on the inside.  I should have known better than to buy an oven so cheaply made'),
(1440, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-10', 'Five Stars great machine'),
(1441, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Great quality, brews a great cup. We love our Cuisinart DCC-3000. It has all the features we need, without all the extra widgets we don\'t. The build quality is excellent, and it makes an excellent cup of coffee.'),
(1442, 12, 1, 4, '2014-04-14', 'Very good use to reheat kids meal and toaster works very well I bought this product to preheat pizzas and wings and other food for my child. It serves the purpose. I like the toaster too'),
(1443, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-22', 'Highly recommended I have had this toaster oven for about five years. We use it daily. I\'m ordering a new one today even though the old one still works great. Just want to have a back up. Who knows? The first one could last five more years!.'),
(1444, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-13', 'who knew coffee could taste this good After months of going back and forth reading everyones reviews on various coffee makers I decided to go with this one and it is FANTASTIC.  I have used it a week with no trouble.  Being 55 I can honestly say that this Hamilton trumps all the coffee makers I have ever had.  I would not hesitate to buy this one as it works as if it were much more expensive.'),
(1445, 2, 1, 2, '2015-12-18', 'Careful...Got a Flimsy Knock-Off I like the one we bought at Macy\'s, but not the one we received from Amazon, which was a knock-off, complete with knock-off logo and made of cheaper materials. We had intended to give away our old one from Macy\'s and keep the new one, but the quality of this knock-off was so sub-bar, we gave it away. It would better to list knock-offs with different logos (evidence of \"different manufacturers\") in separate Amazon listings so we know exactly what we\'re getting.'),
(1446, 4, 1, 1, '2015-06-11', 'DANGEROUS PRODUCT!!  DO NOT BUY! DANGEROUS PRODUCT!!  DO NOT BUY!  After only two years of using this product, if the toaster oven is plugged in, it automatically heats all elements to combustion. It will not stop heating and heating and heating until it is unplugged.  With lots of kids in the house continually heating up frozen pizzas and such, this toaster oven by Cuisinart TOB-40 is so incredibly dangerous that it has been removed from the premises.  It was a wonderful oven until the on/off switch stopped working and the unit continued to heat and heat and heat.  Luckily, we realized what was happening and quickly unplugged the unit.  Don\'t buy.  Definite fire hazard.'),
(1447, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-08', 'The best Love it!'),
(1448, 4, 1, 1, '2015-12-12', 'Short life span / uneven toasting We purchased the toaster oven in June of 2013, and stopped worked a couple of months ago (shortly after the 2-year warranty).  Our main use was for toasting bread, and one reason why we bought the oven was because the advertisement read consistent toasting every time.  Well, it was not consistent, and have since noticed that they advertise of the packaging that you will get a consistent toast (or bake).  So, between the short life time for a toaster that should last 10 years, and the inconsistency in it\'s toasting ability, it gets a one star.  However, if you do not need a long lasting toaster oven and don\'t mind the differences in toasting quality, then the pull out shelf, and the single push button for toasting are nice features that I am very surprised are not incorporated into other toaster/ovens in this price range.'),
(1449, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'It is very nice to be able to make your own cup and ... Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review. We purchased the 2.0 Brewing system for our office.  We have people that drink tea and coffee, we have a 5 person office.  It is very nice to be able to make your own cup and not have to brew a whole pot and throw the rest out.  It is very cost efficient and I love the option to get hot water. I also thought that the filter was easy to install and you know the water is filtered.  When I purchased the Keurig it was on sale which made it even more worth the purchase.  We are probably going to purchase the brewer thermal craft for meetings in the office.'),
(1450, 6, 1, 1, '2014-12-16', 'Cheap junk I\'ve owned this model\'s predecessor (Cuisinart 4-slice toaster with a white plastic exterior) for at least 12 years, and it\'s worked great until the past several months when various heating parts started to quit.  This new model is just cheap junk.  The levers are flimsy, and one doesn\'t latch at the bottom at all.  One knob is so tight that it\'s difficult to turn, and the other is so loose that it\'s nearly falling off.  I didn\'t actually toast with it because the defective lever mandates a return to Amazon. What happened to Cuisinart\'s manufacturing standards?'),
(1451, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-07', 'Good machine Good machine good taste');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1452, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-07', 'Pleased with this purchase! I moved to a country that doesn\'t always supply ovens in the apartments because most of the country doesn\'t bake anything. This is a life saver! It works well and I love the digital features. I would recommend it to anyone as an oven or if you\'re just looking for a quality toaster oven. *Note to those using it internationally: Black & Decker warns that on first use you may smell some dust burning and this in normal. HOWEVER, if you smell something burning and the smell gets stronger (does not dissipates) and you start to SEE SMOKE, you should immediately unplug it from the 1KVA transformer box BEFORE you start a FIRE!!! After I unplugged it from the smoking and just about to light on fire transformer, I plugged it into a 2KVA transformer box which has been able to handle the workload ever since! :)'),
(1453, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-01', 'Mine works fine with third party coffee I recently picked this up for 60 percent off.  I was upgrading from the regular Keurig with a reservoir.  I was hesitant because it\'s a well known fact that third party coffee won\'t work. This is not the case which is why the product gets a 5.  I drink my Electric City coffee all the time.  Sometimes I\'ll have to rotate the cup a bit but it typically gives me no problems. My fav thing about upgrading is the option to make your coffee strong. Overall this is a good buy if you really adore coffee.  Otherwise,  go with a cheaper models.  You will not regret getting one'),
(1454, 1, 1, 4, '2016-08-19', 'Recommend this Kuerig but make sure you use pods with the Kuerig markings on the rim of the pod. My old Kuerig pump clogged or failed and I bought this to replace. I agree with other users, the product works very well.  It has a nice big reservoir to hold water for about 4-5 cups of coffee. You can use the carafe and larger mugs with this version. Like others, I don\'t like that you have to use Kuerig cups that are marked on the rim.  If you buy coffee that does not have the Kuerig markings on the top rim of the pod then it will not work.  Like others have found, this can be worked around by taping an old rim onto the pod.  I understand Kuerig is trying to control the consistency of the coffee used in their makers but this is a real hassle.  It seems a cheap way for them to get licensing fees or whatever.'),
(1455, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-05', 'First Impression Review I have finally found a coffee maker that makes coffee the way I like it and brings back memories of my favorite coffee maker, the Braun KF180 FlavorSelect. Braun decided not to make the coffee maker that I would still be using, today,  but Hamilton Beach has created a suitable replacement that may even go the KF180 one better in a few of the convenience areas. I make my coffee in an open area on a peninsula, so I don\'t really need the removable water reservoir... I just bring my pitcher of filtered water to the dance, direct from it\'s location. The brew strength selector is SO much easier than my last $90 coffee maker that required all sorts of soft menus on a tiny and very dim screen... pressing the mode button six times and so on. Never could keep that one straight, so I never cried when it recently failed about a year or so after purchase. This carafe pour spout has so far not dribbled a drop of coffee down the side of the carafe or on my counter top, like the $90 model did in abundance. Finally, a clean coffee area... well, relatively clean. Even before I tried both normal size brew strength settings I could tell that the bold setting was selected to bring out the flavor of my Ethiopian Yirgacheffe coffee. The \"keep warm\" setting is likewise very easy to adjust, with stupid proof graphic interface to show you the settings. The clock in the digital screen is as easy to set as the one in my 2000 model pickup truck (hour and minute buttons), and it can be seen very easily when I first enter the kitchen in bright blue numbers. I don\'t really need a clock on my coffee pot, but I just hate seeing a flashing 1200, or the wrong time on a clock. On this machine, this task is easy. The bottom of the coffee maker has a base that easily rotates on my counter, to make adding water very easy from the side of the reservoir. The basket style coffee filter holder is easy to remove and take to a location so I can pour the ground coffee from the grinder catch container and avoid the potential of grounds going places I don\'t want them, in the maker itself. The first pot I brewed, I immediately dropped a thermometer in the drip hole and pulled it out...  when it went just past 180, after the brewing was done... that is my favorite carafe temp, which is very different from the temperature of extraction for those who consider 200 degrees in the carafe as perfection. That means at least some of the water was most likely past the boiling  point when it hit the grounds. That removes some of the more volatile flavor notes that I have come to appreciate. I don\'t pay for EY coffee beans just to ruin the flavor during brewing. The carafe is easily moved to and from it\'s perch in the machine, even when filled with coffee, which was not the case with my now expired $90 coffee maker. Finally summing up... this little $45 beauty ranks right beside my previous and more expensive favorite, but now extinct coffee maker, and well above the next in line. If this one lasts a decent amount of time and isn\'t replaced by Hamilton Beach with a piece of junk, it could be my favorite of all time. I called this a first impression review, so if longevity becomes a problem, I will be back to set that record straight, if I can overcome the depression of my loss long enough to post again. Coffee makers are very personal, and important to people who love their coffee. That\'s me.'),
(1456, 7, 3, 5, '2016-05-25', 'I\'ve wanted a coffeemaker that uses K cups ever since I had a cup served to me during a meeting. The coffee was restaurant quality from the K cup so even though there were some less than favorable reviews, I purchased the coffee maker brand that starts with a \"K\". I had nothing but trouble with it from the start. I called the company and they made it sound like it was the user\'s fault. I wasted a ton of K-cups trying to get it to work and finally brought it back to the store. I decided to try this Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve and thought if it doesn\'t work, I\'m giving up on the K cup idea. I am extremely happy with it. It\'s half the size of the other brand I had and fits really well on my counter. I\'ve had nothing but great cups of coffee from it. It\'s a relaxing experience brewing a fresh cup in the morning - unlike the stress I had with the other coffee maker. I would definitely recommend this brewer. It was $20 less than the brand I took back also!'),
(1457, 7, 3, 3, '2015-01-09', 'does not actually do larger cups (not ounce wize but size yes)'),
(1458, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-15', 'Five Stars Wonderful toaster'),
(1459, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-16', 'but didn\'t have room for both a toaster and toaster oven on the counter - this works beautifully! We use a toaster oven frequently, but didn\'t have room for both a toaster and toaster oven on the counter - this works beautifully!.'),
(1460, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-20', 'Works well It works pretty good for the price. No surprises.'),
(1461, 4, 1, 1, '2015-11-14', 'Heating element warped and cracked open, posing a fire ... Heating element warped and cracked open, posing a fire danger once it collapses.  Dangerous product that failed way too soon.'),
(1462, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-01', 'This coffee make failed today, July 1, 2015 ... This coffee make failed today, July 1, 2015.  I bought it in January 2015.  Out of warranty, no return per return policy.  This is the last Hamilton Beach product that I will ever buy. I would give it ZERO stars if possible.'),
(1463, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Five Stars Coffee made under 5 minutes!'),
(1464, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-04', 'One Star Do not waste your money. Buy the ninja for $20 more dollars!'),
(1465, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-12', 'Not real powerful but good enough for smoothies I abuse this blender and it has worked well for the year that I have had it. Not real powerful but good enough for smoothies.'),
(1466, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-23', 'Four Stars I like this little guy. It\'s small, compact and powerful (surprise!).'),
(1467, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-21', 'Only for making toast This is good if you only want to toast something otherwise it is pretty useless; I use my toaster oven daily to cook, .  Whenever I cooked chicken or fish, it got grease spatters everywhere which were impossible to clean off.  I\'ve had it 3 months and it is going to be recycled today.  Had a similar Cuisinart toaster oven for 4-5 years and the coating on the front and inside the top became burned and was peeling off (looked like peeling paint) so I replaced it w/ this one which was a huge mistake.  Bought yet another one that just arrived, the TOB-135, on a friend\'s recommendation; hope this works out better.  Have tried many other brands and found that Cuisinart, in spite of the issues I\'m having is better than most.'),
(1468, 12, 1, 2, '2016-09-19', 'No oven timer / really small oven compartment I have a narrow spot where I want to put a toaster oven but not something that takes up a lot of space. I was hoping this would fit the bill but I\'m going to have to return it for a couple reasons: 1. No oven timer! The toaster function automatically pops the toast after a set time, but the oven just stays on until user turns it off. That seems really dangerous if you ask me. What they should do is have the toaster knob function as dual duty and serve as a timer during oven operation. I assumed that was how it worked until I found out otherwise. 2. The oven compartment is really, really small, smaller than it appears in the photo. I\'d be mostly using it for mini-pizzas which would just barely fit, my bigger concern being that the top of the food would get overdone since the top burner is so close to the food and there is no way to set the oven to just use the lower burners. I\'ll be returning and just getting a somewhat small toaster oven. Not much bigger on the outside but way bigger on the inside. Good idea, but another product where 2 in 1 just ends up being a compromise for both of the combined features...'),
(1469, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'AWESOME GIFT!! This was a Christmas Gift for a loved one........ THEY ARE IN LOVE WITH IT!!!!!!!!!!  So, happy to be able to find the perfect gift for this young lady ! She\'s one happy gal!  :-D'),
(1470, 4, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Tray Me Tray below is awesome.'),
(1471, 5, 1, 2, '2015-08-25', 'the carafe breaks extremely easily and you will have to pay $20+ to replace ... BEWARE: the carafe breaks extremely easily and you will have to pay $20+ to replace it'),
(1472, 4, 1, 2, '2016-01-18', 'The oven seems fine as does the broiler The range on the toast markings is all F\'d up. Light is as burnt as can be. We had to make ourown mark on the dial to get a consistant setting. Any variation of 1 or more results in hardly toasted to burnt. The oven seems fine as does the broiler.'),
(1473, 7, 3, 5, '2014-01-19', 'Great option for K cups. It also uses ground coffee as well as K cups. I\'m glad I bought it.'),
(1474, 2, 1, 1, '2016-06-25', 'One Star no heat on, so returned.'),
(1475, 7, 3, 4, '2016-01-10', 'I picked up this coffee maker about a week ago and overall I\'m satisfied. I\'ve only used it for K-cups so far and it brews great coffee in about 2 minutes, it\'s really easy to use and takes up less counter space than the Keurig and costs half as much. The reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 is because it can be a bit messy and difficult to get the k-cup out, also it only holds 8oz of water which isn\'t enough to fill a large coffee mug or travel mug, I expected a larger reservoir since it has a bigger basket for ground coffee. The first couple brews had kind of a plastic taste to them, but after that it tasted great, I would recommend running straight water through it for about 3 brews before you use it. I think the negative reviewers just got a defective unit, mine doesn\'t leak or make the K-cups explode.'),
(1476, 5, 1, 1, '2014-02-22', 'A PIECE OF JUNK I BOUGHT THIS, AND AT FIRST WAS VERY SATISFIED.  HOWEVER, IT ABRUPTLY QUICK WORKING. I HAD TO CONTACT THE COMPANY DIRECTLY ON-LINE.  THEY REPLACED IT, BUT I HAD TO PAY S&H. AGAIN, I WAS HAPPY...FOR A WHILE.  I NOTICED THAT IT WAS VERY NOISY, AND SOUNDED LIKE A CHOO-CHOO TRAIN NEAR THE END OF THE PERKING PERIOD. THEN IT SUDDENLY QUICK AGAIN. OUT OF FRUSTRATION, I TOSSED IT INTO THE RECYCLE BIN AND  BOUGHT A DIFFERENT BRAND. MY CONFIDENCE IN THE HAMILTON BEACH PRODUCTS IS  GONE!'),
(1477, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Five Stars works great does bagels very well'),
(1478, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-18', 'The front swing out basket makes it easy to fill AND EMPTY This is the most convenient coffee pot I have ever had.  The design of this coffee pot is superb.  The front swing out basket makes it easy to fill AND EMPTY.  The water reservoir quantity markings are visible without my glasses and the fact that you can pop the lid at the top to fill makes it so much easier.  I just fill from my Brita Filter pitcher and I don\'t even need to pull the reservoir out of the pot.  And after all of this, the coffee tastes great.  I prefer strong coffee.  This \'bold\' brew intensity gives me that yet saves me at least one scoop of coffee each time.  So over a month\'s time that adds up and saves me money on coffee grinds.  I would definitely recommend this Hamilton Beach coffee maker.'),
(1479, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-30', 'Great for the Price Wanted a good toaster oven for the office. This was just it a good quality name brand toaster we have used several times.'),
(1480, 4, 1, 2, '2015-03-29', 'Worked until it broke... This unit stood up to just over a year of solid use. I had looked and looked for a toaster that turned on with a button, the cheaper model I had prior to this was the kind with the dial that ticks down, and I always had inconsistent results. This toaster, by and large, made good toast/sandwiches/heated food of various types... But a few weeks ago, the mechanism that controls the door opening began to get sticky. We tried to see if it was bent inside, or what was going on with it, and that helped for a short while. Eventually you had to start to yank on it to get it open. And then I pulled one morning, and the door exploded. I had to laugh at myself standing in the kitchen just holding the broken handle, but for the retail price, this shouldn\'t have happened. Poor design.'),
(1481, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-08', 'Good for a low cost toaster oven It toasts a ... Good for a low cost toaster oven It toasts a little unevenly but not too much.  will handle 3-4 pieces of pizza'),
(1482, 3, 1, 4, '2015-06-30', 'Four Stars Really big, but a very high quality toaster.'),
(1483, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-07', 'Five Stars Toasts bread to perfection!'),
(1484, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-18', 'I like you can program it for the next morning Keeps coffee hot a long time. I like you can program it for the next morning. Good buy.'),
(1485, 10, 1, 2, '2015-12-31', 'Not Even Worth $15 Bought this because I was looking for an inexpensive blender to make smoothies, I wish I\'d have spent the extra money for a blender thatactually works! It chops and blends ice or frozen fruit, but only halfway. Be prepared to have lots of hard chunks in your smoothie whether using ice or frozen fruit. I even tried blending it for much longer periods of time and shaking/turning the blender so all contents could be exposed to the blades. That didn\'t work. After too long I end up with a liquid juice drink, not a smoothie.. But I liquid drink that still contains lots of hard chuncks if fruit/ or ice. Spend the extra money for better quality!'),
(1486, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-04', 'This is the best toaster oven I have owned (and I\'ve owned a ... This is the best toaster oven I have owned (and I\'ve owned a couple). My last one was by Black and Decker, so I decided to go with the brand again. This toaster oven has more bells and whistles than my last one, and it looks good in my kitchen.'),
(1487, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-19', 'This thing is a piece of junk. 3 temperature ... This thing is a piece of junk. 3 temperature dials from the seventies that all have to be turned on or it doesn\'t work? No thanks.'),
(1488, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-15', 'Here is why this one is superior: easy clean up I\'ll keep it short: this coffee maker is everything it\'s cracked up to be.  I had a fancy coffee maker for years --- you know, the kind that grinds your beans.  Here is why this one is superior: easy clean up, hotter coffee, carafe that doesn\'t drip while pouring, removable reservoir, and regular/bold brewing settings.  This coffee pot has so far lived up to all the hype!'),
(1489, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'satisfied Really like the convenience of the one serving cup with travel lid. Blender works good so far with meal replacement shakes. Still have yet to try fruit smootie.'),
(1490, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-11', 'In with the new but still keeping the old. I\'ve had my keurig 2.0 for around a week now and have really been enjoying it. It\'s taking some getting used to though. My old keurig didn\'t have a water tank so I never had to worry about descaling it but there is some convenience to the tank in that the water is always preheated so my coffee is ready almost immediately. The touch screen is cool with a few different settings for size, strength of your drink, and even a setting specifically for hot cocoa. I haven\'t purchased a carafe yet but it might be something I consider in the future for when I have company. My biggest complaint is that you cannot use third part \"k-cups\" and my favorite coffee happens to be from a non-keurig brand. I know there are hacks and things you can do to get around that but if you\'re talking about a $100 piece of equipment you probably don\'t want to risk breaking it. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review! I received this product free for testing from influenster in exchange for my honest opinion.'),
(1491, 9, 1, 3, '2016-04-11', 'Sadly disappointed.  Hoped for remedial suggestions. Not satisfied.  Strong tendency to overflow.  Quite frustrating.  When called Cuisinart instructed that I should  return to Amazon.  No mention of possible solution.  Prior experience with this mfgr. Much more attentive !'),
(1492, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-17', 'One of the best coffee makers out there I have tried other brands of coffee makers but I always go back to Hamilton Beach.  One of the best coffee makers out there.  This is the first of this model I have tried and I think it is my favorite.  So easy to use, coffee is fantastic, no drip carafe.  I absolutely love this coffeemaker.  Highly recommend it.'),
(1493, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-22', 'Five Stars Bottom line great coffee pot and a great price'),
(1494, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-27', 'Five Stars Good product.'),
(1495, 8, 1, 3, '2014-12-11', 'Three Stars good enough for 2 people.  the only drawback, is that it does not shut off itself.  :-('),
(1496, 4, 1, 5, '2016-05-10', 'Good value/Great product I\'ve been using this for almost a year now and love the features it offers.  The alert for done toast is loud and can be heard from a few rooms away which I find invaluable.  Its easy to keep clean and shows no sign of wear after a year.  I would order again.'),
(1497, 12, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Five Stars delivered quickly ... very impressed'),
(1498, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-04', 'Best blender you can get for this amazing price. For the price, this is absolutely the best blender you can get. It\'s durable, mixes well, and isn\'t very loud. It\'s easy to clean and doesn\'t hold bad smells in if you leave stuff in there too long (this may only be something I do). The only time I ever had an issue was when I tried to make flour out of wheat berries in this. It couldn\'t handle it and stuff started spewing out the back of it. But that was my fault. Another thing is that the lid isn\'t very tight, so liquids can still get out of it if you hold it upside down or spill it, so just be careful of that.'),
(1499, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'Five Stars Bought it for my 84 year old father.  He loves it.  Simple to use.'),
(1500, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Great little oven An advantage of this small oven is that it heats up and cooks quickly.  I use a temp lower than recommended for cooking, and when reheating: from frozen pizza slice to plate in 5 mins or less.  And it doesn\'t flip the toast across the room at pop-up.'),
(1501, 3, 1, 1, '2016-10-09', 'One Star GAVE IT TO MY GRANDDAUGHTER  TOO HARD TO READ THE SETTINGS.'),
(1502, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-17', 'Five Stars Great. We\'re much happier with it than other coffee makers we\'ve purchased for twice the price.'),
(1503, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-17', 'Good quality for the price Works well.  Good quality for the price.'),
(1504, 11, 1, 1, '2014-10-06', 'To small It\'s really to small. Won\'t fit a frozen pizza. The dials are also a real pain. Makes it hard to just use it as a toaster. I should have returned it but didn\'t really get around to trying it for a couple months after I bought it. Bought a bigger better one at Costco. AT least there if you don\'t like something a week or even a year later you can take it back. I love Amazon Prime but you better be sure you like it real quick.'),
(1505, 2, 1, 3, '2016-04-06', 'Pretty okay oven. Great for the price! My 9 yo asked for her own oven for Christmas.  She loves making muffins etc. but is a bit intimidated by working over the large oven door.  This toaster oven has been alternative.  I can\'t give it more stars because the distance from the rack to the top of the oven is so limited that the muffin tops almost hit, making the baking a bit uneven.  It is perfect for re-heating pizza.  Also the tray that came with the oven is the material that, when placed in the dishwasher, now turns everything it touches BLACK.'),
(1506, 4, 1, 1, '2016-11-20', 'Not a good buy I have the model 30 BW.  It is just over 4 years old and the Teflon coating on the insides and back is flaking off.  The inside top and bottom have no Teflon coating.  The problem is that when these flakes land on the heating rods they give off a toxic gas which has been known to kill birds and give humans flue like systems.  Teflon melts at a temperature of 662 degrees F, 330 degrees C. I contacted Cuisinart and said we can\'t help you because it is out of warranty.'),
(1507, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-22', 'Great little blender ! Very good  little blender. have mixed fresh fruit with frozen fruit , even a few ice cubes and does the job. Just pulse it and don\'t run it continuously and you will be fine. Only had it for a few weeks but happy so far. Hope it will hold up over time. Love the compact size.'),
(1508, 3, 1, 1, '2016-07-13', 'This is my 3rd Black and Decker Toaster Oven over ... This is my 3rd Black and Decker Toaster Oven over the last 20 years.  I stayed with this brand because of past success. This model was disappointing. It does not turn itself off (i.e. if you set the toast cycle to 3, the taste oven will never turn off when the food item is toasted to level 3.  I have to watch the item and then unplug every time. So far everything I have made was burned quickly and I have to pull the plug to stop the toaster from over heating.'),
(1509, 5, 1, 5, '2014-05-11', 'Great coffee maker The best part about this coffee maker is the carafe.  It is very well designed.  The carafe fits your hand and pours without spilling.  We really like the large top opening for pouring in the water.  A plus is the fact that it can easily be removed to fill at the tap.  The filter basket is easy to use.  When scoping in the coffee in our old unit, there was always the risk of getting coffee in the water resevoir.  Not so with the Hamilton Beach. Oh, one more thing.  It makes great coffee!'),
(1510, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-04', 'Mom bought for my Mom who lives in an apartment and it works out great for her and a small space_.'),
(1511, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-16', 'Five Stars Works awesome and super convenient . decent quality for the price.'),
(1512, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'Five Stars I\'m very satisfied!'),
(1513, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-23', 'Great toaster oven with all the features! This is exactly what we were looking for. Some of the more costly toaster ovens did not even have a timer. This has a great look and great price point for the features.'),
(1514, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-18', 'Brews good coffee. Faceplate fell off though Brews good coffee. Faceplate fell off though.'),
(1515, 4, 1, 4, '2015-07-01', 'Toaster Oven > Toaster  -  always I have always been one to prefer a toaster oven over a toaster, it just has so much more versatility. Also, it\'s nice to not have to heat up the entire oven to bake something small. Everything with them product has been great so far, I have had it about a month with no complaints. I have used it to reheat individual slices of pizza and it worked great for that. It cooks frozen foods at the same speed of a regular oven, so that is really helpful as well! I\'m a bit worried about longevity because many people have stated concerns about it breaking. Will be making sure I know the rules of the warranty.'),
(1516, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love this coffee pot Love this coffee pot! Finally no pouring of water into the murky bowels of the coffee maker, but instead the sanitary and lovely removeable water reservoir. Truly dripless when getting a cup mid-brew. Easy to clean. Great price. Highly recommended.'),
(1517, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-21', 'The machine itself is touch style which I personally do not like. As with every Keurig product I have purchased The new style is slightly wider and seems clunkier than the old model which fit perfectly in the narrow space I had.  The water filter which has to be prepared and inserted in the water tank is very difficult to install. I ended up calling to find out how since the cap of my filter would not come off as shown by the poorly written and badly illustrated instructions, separate for the water filter.  I was told to run the outside of the water filter under warm water for a minute or so and the tabs would loosen up.  I should not have had to do this, and if it was absolutely necessary to design the filter in such a difficult style, the instructions should have included this very important tip.  The machine itself is touch style which I personally do not like.  As with every Keurig product I have purchased, the instructions were not understandable, needlessly confusing, missing crucial information and badly illustrated.  The machine works so I gave it a 3.'),
(1518, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-07', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker, pot doesn\'t leak when you pour, and it gets the coffee very hot!'),
(1519, 6, 1, 1, '2015-05-15', 'Save your money Very disappointed. I threw out my old toaster because of uneven cooking. This one is even worse--frozen waffles end up soggy on one side and burnt on the other. Bagels fared somewhat better but still had burned spots. I can only imagine that higher heat settings would incinerate whatever was in the toaster as my problems occurred at a 3 or less!'),
(1520, 3, 1, 4, '2016-01-08', 'Good little oven I bought this oven for our travel trailer, since the oven in the camper didn\'t cook evenly.  It\'s got plenty of different functions, and is very easy to use.  The temperature seems accurate, and it cooks evenly, so I\'m happy.'),
(1521, 6, 1, 3, '2015-06-08', 'Like the handle feature that raises the toast higher for ... Toasts a little unevenly. Like the handle feature that raises the toast higher for small pieces.'),
(1522, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', '... my mom when hers died after 2 (she took poor care of it) I had the same Kuerig for over 4 years in college and passed it along to my mom when hers died after 2 (she took poor care of it). I was hesitant to get a new Kuerig, thinking nothing could compare to my old one, but I absolutely love my Kuerig 2.0! Thanks, Kuerig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1523, 8, 1, 5, '2015-07-30', 'Five Stars very good coffee. just the right size.'),
(1524, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Saves time and Coffee! This Keurig gets the job done. For a young couple that is on the run in the morning, this has solved the coffee dilemma. The two of used to have to make 2 different pots for 2 different roasts. Now it\'s as simple as changing a pod. And to think...I got this machine free for testing!'),
(1525, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-30', 'Good Product Just right for an old couple like us'),
(1526, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-12', 'good product, good price'),
(1527, 11, 1, 1, '2016-06-16', 'We loved it for a solid 5 weeks We loved it for a solid 5 weeks.  Unfortunately it started not working consistently at around six weeks.  At first I thought it was just me, but then finally my husband mentioned it too.  Not heating consistently, sometimes not heating up enough, sometimes not at all.  Presently it only works about 2/3 of the time.'),
(1528, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-14', 'Perfect Works perfectly, it has a lot of temperature options, very easy to use and very easy to clean. i love it.'),
(1529, 8, 1, 3, '2016-04-18', 'Great for a nice large single serving Tinier than I thought. Great for a nice large single serving. Not suitable for a two person coffee-drinking household.'),
(1530, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Best Ever! Love my new machine!! It doesn\'t make near the noise that the old version makes, and it\'s fast!! It even gives me little greetings like \'Welcome\' and \'Enjoy\'. I am a seriously happy camper!!! And FYI, if you buy this new machine, and your old pods dont work, they fix it! FREE! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(1531, 2, 1, 2, '2015-01-17', 'Cord is ridiculously short If your electrical outlet is very, very close to where you will put this item then this might be a great product. Unfortunately, mine was not. I think they carried the short cord for safety sake to a ridiculous extreme on this unit. I understand the theory but I think it needs to be practical. A really short cord on a toaster is less of a problem because it has a smaller countertop footprint. Larger physical dimensions will generally reduce the countertop options that you have.'),
(1532, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-02', 'I had been wanting to get a single-serve coffee maker, but was concerned about all the K-cups I\'d be adding to the trash; I already have a coffee maker, an espresso machine, and an iced coffee maker, so I decided that should do me. This, however, solved my K-cup concerns--you can use either the pods (which are so very easy!) or you can remove the pod holder and use just the filter for coffee grounds. You can also make either a regular cup of coffee by raising the base up, or you can make a travel-mug sized drink by lowering it back down. There\'s no chance of overflows because you use the cup to measure the water in. It\'s so simple: decide on the size and type of drink you are going to make, pour in the water, insert either the pod or measure in the coffee, close the top, press the start button, and in about a minute you have hot coffee, tea, cocoa, or any of the wide range of drinks you can make with the pods. Add creamer, sweetener, whatever you want, and that\'s it! I\'m so happy with it--if I want coffee quick to go in the morning and there isn\'t any made, I put it all together and by the time I grab my things and lock the door, it\'s ready. I love it!'),
(1533, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-18', 'how has this machine gotten worse in the last 10 years huge, noisy, and difficult to control. we end up burning toast half the time. how has this machine gotten worse in the last 10 years?? some thing are better before they are \"improved\".'),
(1534, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-23', 'Five Stars Nice toaster and fast delivery.'),
(1535, 7, 3, 4, '2016-01-08', 'This coffeemaker does work with K cups. I like that you can use your travel cup, but you can only put 8 ounces of water in the back. Not enough to fill the travel cup.'),
(1536, 4, 1, 4, '2016-02-28', 'Solid performer This toaster oven has performed well so far.  It is an upgrade from the one I had before in that it keeps it\'s own time based on manual settings instead of relying on a wind-up spring dial.  I mainly use of to make toast.  It does that acceptably once the proper settings are arrived at through experimentation.  It has enough room to make other things and can certainly reheat a couple slices of pizza or the like.  It is compact and fits in the enclosure I have.  On the whole I\'m pleased.  I\'ve yet to find or hear of a toast oven that is optimized to make toast and this one isn\'t either.  But it is a solid performer.'),
(1537, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-01', 'Love it! It is an update version of my ... Love it!  It is an update version of my old one!  It has better buttons that work better and the manual really does explain how to use it.  Learned new ways to make it work for me.  Better then using Big Energy in the regular oven'),
(1538, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-13', 'I like this. I like this.. everything is what I needed/ wanted except for 2 minor inconveniences: The 2\' cord is 1\' shorter than needed for the spot it was supposed to go. luckily, I did find a workable spot that looks okay and isn\'t in the way. the second is the knob that you turn way to the right and then back to where you need it to regulate timing of toasting (browning)..very hard turning back! I\'ll live with this, as long as arthritis doesn\'t mess with my hands too much.'),
(1539, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-08', 'Five Stars I like this little guy. It gurgles and shakes and has a real personality.'),
(1540, 12, 1, 4, '2015-04-20', 'Fits Our Needs Quite Well Is it \"perfect\"? No, but it suits our needs better than any other similar product. We had one for about 5 years, switch was wearing out. We had no interest in looking at anything else.'),
(1541, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-30', 'The toastest with the mostest. This is a great toaster.  I am very happy with it so far.'),
(1542, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-07', 'Works well and looks nice Works well, looks nice on counter, glad I got it.'),
(1543, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-30', 'Easy to clean Easy to clean, coffee is great, does exactly what the seller says it will.. The fuel style gauge and and cup lighting make this unit a five star product.  Nice trick with the {1-4 cup button}, selecting that will just make the brew stronger regardless of how many cups you are actually making.  Saves a little money / coffee in my opinion.'),
(1544, 3, 1, 4, '2015-11-12', 'Four Stars Great product. Serves its purpose and cooks everything great!'),
(1545, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Toastation Tradition The Toastation was a gift for my daughter.  She loves it !  The tradition continues because she loved mine__.'),
(1546, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-15', 'Five Stars Love this thing. It\'s great for quick shakes and smoothies.'),
(1547, 10, 1, 4, '2015-05-19', 'Four Stars great for a quick protein shake'),
(1548, 7, 3, 1, '2016-05-31', 'DO NOT BUY THIS MACHINE. I purchase this on 2015 Nov 08. It stopped working Around 2016 Jan 20. (3 months) Received a new one after paying a small for shipping fee (no other charge), around Jan 31. It stopped working again 2016 May 30. (4 months) Issue: The water does not pump up after boiling = Useless. Do not waste your money. It\'s stressful to deal with warranty and the lack of coffee when you need it and the lack of such for a few days while waiting for replacement? If this happens once, okay, twice... it\'s ridiculous.'),
(1549, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-01', 'Great basic Keurig!  Simple to use. I gave it to my wife to take to work.  WHAT A MORALE BOOSTER!  She found out that a couple of her work mates were thinking about it, but mere timid due to management.  My wife simply brought it in on a Sunday shift with a case of \"Krazy Cups\".  Management?  They not only didn\'t mind, they have been \"caught\" using it too!'),
(1550, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-29', 'Five Stars Great coffee pot.'),
(1551, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-26', 'Four Stars Just received my new toaster oven so far I have no complains'),
(1552, 4, 1, 1, '2017-01-28', 'Do NOT buy this dangerous fire hazard!!!! I would like to clearly state I did NOT buy this item on Amazon. I bought it from Bed Bath and Beyond so this review is strictly on the item itself, not anything to do with Amazon. I purchased this same model and had the same experiences that most others had. First the front bottom element warped and became a source of uneven heating to anything that we put in it. Then the rear bottom element just stopped working completely. Now today the previously warped element started sparking and caught on fire, spreading to the food inside. When I attempted to unplug the toaster oven I was electrically shocked. How Cuisinart can still be in business after the ridiculous number of these complaints is beyond me. This is a very dangerous fire hazard that could burn down a house and potentially injure or kill to people.'),
(1553, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-20', 'I absolutely love this coffee maker I absolutely love this coffee maker. The dispenser is such a brilliant feature, just pop your mug underneath, press and voila. No carafes to wash. Very happy with it!'),
(1554, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-19', 'One Star A complete lemon; did not last 6 months'),
(1555, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'LOVE THIS MACHINE! I bought a this about 2 weeks ago and I LOVE it!  You sure can\'t beat the convenience of this machine, however it really did make a point in my mind of how lazy we have become as a society!  It was very easy to set up and use for the first time without any prior knowledge about Keurig systems at all, and is very easy to use and maintain everyday.  It makes a great, hot, cup of coffee and the amount of different flavors you can get is amazing.  The only thing I am disappointed in with the 2.0 system is that Keurig has rigged it so that you CANNOT use off brands of kcups.  I don\'t think that is right.  There are several hacks on YTube, however, that show you how to get around this snag quite easily, so Keurig shouldn\'t have done it in the first place.'),
(1556, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-19', 'Gave as gift.... I gave this toaster oven to a friend, who had never used one before.  I\'ve always loved mine and now she loves hers!'),
(1557, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'I LOVE MY KEURIG I LOVE MY KEURIG!! I wanted one for my college dorm room because trekking across campus for coffee in the snow is not fun! This model is sleek and sophisticated and not what every student has in their dorm (which was what I wanted). This model also was tall enough to fit most of my travel mugs which the regular dorm size is not big enough to do, and as a college student you always are drinking your coffee on the go! All in all it is a great machine and model!! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1558, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-17', 'Great coffeemaker We\'re very particular with coffee and have been buying used, Braun coffeemakers for years, because they made such good coffee.  We had a Krups, but it only lasted a few months, and the coffee was never as good.  Hamilton Beach seemed unlikely to make a good replacement for our old favorite, but was well-rated.  Turns out it makes really good coffee, is easy to use and program, and is very easy to fill.  It\'s a little bigger, but that\'s part of what makes it easier to fill without spilling water and making coffee ground mess (it spins around and has a removable tank).'),
(1559, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-18', 'Great coffee LOVE this coffee maker .... so glad we found it'),
(1560, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-09', 'PERFECT TOASTER. No complaints. LOVE THIS TOASTER. It\'s prefect for my wife and I in our little apartment. We don\'t have a ton of counter space and turning on the oven heats the whole place so this is nice since we don\'t have a microwave and there\'s no other option to reheat stuff.'),
(1561, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-19', 'Five Stars Nice roster, very easy to use. I bought it as a gift for my friend.'),
(1562, 1, 1, 1, '2016-04-30', 'Junk. This thing is annoying. My partner bought it for me and thought she was doing something nice for me. Unfortunately the thing is just a source of aggravation. I mostly only use it on the weekends, when I have time to idle and enjoy my coffee but: 1) The stupid 2.0 DRM forced me to trick it so I could use some coffee we had brought to the cabin for the weekend (My partner and son-in-law both have the earlier Kuerigs that I bought for them) 2) It comes with a special \"tool\" to unclog it. To me that\'s a bad sign. And sure enough, you have to use it periodically, because it will just chunk-chunk-chunk and sputter and little coffee comes out. 3) Once the display just went dead. It did come back after I left it unplugged for a while. 4) Today, it just goes chunk-chunk-chunk and stops. I used the tool a couple of times and no grounds came out. So...I\'m using the old trusty Mr. Coffee this weekend. Good thing I keep bulk coffee in the house. Kuering. I want a new one.'),
(1563, 5, 1, 4, '2015-12-21', 'The single thing that\'s disappointing was accurately described I read about this coffeemaker on Consumer Reports and decided to buy it regardless. The single thing that\'s disappointing was accurately described: the coffeemaker doesn\'t heat the water to a point that the coffee\'s as hot as it could/should be. Other than this, the coffeemaker\'s great. I like, like, like not having a carafe because the coffee doesn\'t get bitter.'),
(1564, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-28', 'very effective for obliterating edible treats into watery nutrition concoctions this thing is great, makes smoothies and stuff, ya know? i throw a lot of spinach in there and it works great, especially with blue berries a frozen banana and some peach kefir it\'s delicious.'),
(1565, 5, 1, 4, '2014-09-13', 'Just purchased this coffeemaker and I like that it is a compact model and doesn\'t take ... Just purchased this coffeemaker and I like that it is a compact model and doesn\'t take up much room on my counter. Refilling the water is easy and offers you two options- pour directly into the tank or remove the tank and fill.  Options for brewing are easy and I like the \"Keep Warm\" feature.  The only thing I have noticed is that this coffeemaker brews rather slowly compared to others I have owned.'),
(1566, 11, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'works nice! Definitely Decent size oven, fits 4 (regular size) slices of bread, toast evenly, I don\'t care about the marks, i have used it for toasting bread and baking, works nice! Definitely recommend'),
(1567, 12, 1, 3, '2016-01-17', 'After a year and a half the door no longer ... After a year and a half the door no longer stays closed. I am going to have to replace it.'),
(1568, 4, 1, 2, '2015-12-21', 'You just have to manually turn off your toaster which is very annoying in the morning I had this toaster oven since March 2013.  The toast setting failed soon.  No matter where you set your toast setting it would not go off until burning.  You just have to manually turn off your toaster which is very annoying in the morning.'),
(1569, 10, 1, 2, '2015-09-26', 'Not so great Be aware that the plastic used is not the best.  Also, since you can\'t unscrew the blade to wash this, it\'s a pretty tight squeeze even for a bottle brush to try to clean this.  Which means eventually even when you think you\'ve really cleaned it well and let it sit in dish soap solution and really rinsed in hot, once you put the lid on and open it up for next time...put your nose down to it and you can smell it\'s not that clean after many uses.  The motor also can\'t handle much.  I bought a Black and Decker personal one similar to this, it came with two personal bottles and is of higher quality plastic and the blade can be removed for proper cleaning.  So happy with it.'),
(1570, 2, 1, 4, '2015-08-31', 'Four Stars It works!'),
(1571, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'the best.. she loved it the best..she loved it.'),
(1572, 9, 1, 4, '2016-07-06', 'Great coffee, but a few leak issues I love this coffee maker. It can make a quality cup of coffee, and I love how well it keeps the coffee warm without scolding it as my husband and I start our days at different times. The big issue we have is that very occasionally the carafe will leak. It does have a tray to contain any leaks, but a few times this was removed when the leak occurred and we had quite the mess. I have not found this to be tied to any cleaning issues, but it could be user error? Overall, even with a few (or a lot) of drips, we are really happy with the quality of this coffee maker.'),
(1573, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'you enjoy the coffee It made the life easier , just one touch, then in  about 20seconds ,  you enjoy the coffee. No worry about cleaning anything, what you need to do just is to choose your favorite coffee brand . Love it .'),
(1574, 2, 1, 1, '2016-07-06', 'Handle melted off on Warm setting This is a terrible product. I put it on Warm for 20 mins and the handle came completely off. Looks like the plastic threads that hold the screws melted. I have had this for about 7 months only. I also saw that another reviewer had the exact same experience. What kind of an oven doesn\'t have a handle that can withstand heat?'),
(1575, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-29', 'Five Stars works great makes hot coffee would buy again.'),
(1576, 2, 1, 2, '2016-04-24', 'I would not recommend. It makes way too much noise -- ticking sound as it toasts.  Hard to regulate the degree of toastiness you want.  I would not recommend.'),
(1577, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'This is the very best system you I had 2 other Keurig coffee makers ... This is the very best system you I had 2 other Keurig coffee makers I was very unhappy with.'),
(1578, 12, 1, 1, '2016-11-21', 'Dented damaged and scratches? This product was just opened and the box was damaged it was shipped with other items.  The toasterstation is damaged dented and looks almost melted on the bottom and has scratches on it. Very disappointed.'),
(1579, 6, 1, 2, '2015-04-13', 'Not so much. It does not toast evenly.'),
(1580, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-21', 'kudos to the seller my second edit. never thought sellers read reviews, but this one did.  they contacted me to further explain the problem. the c.s. rep called me.....was professional, courteous and ultimately, offered to credit or replace the toaster.  they have achieved loyalty by acting the way all sellers should.  many thanks.  i see that the coil is starting to bubble and a bit hotter in one spot.  that usually means that it\'s about to fail.  have only had it less than 6 months. otherwise, it works to my expectations.  tried 2 or 3 more expensive models and they ran too fast and hot.  that sounds like an advantage, but not when it\'s out of control.  burned my hand with a hot handle. got fed up and went back to an inexpensive model.  besides, toasters get nasty looking very fast and the lower cost makes it easier to replace.  just don\'t know what to replace this one with, after it goes.'),
(1581, 7, 3, 3, '2015-05-22', 'Its a little slow at brewing and makes a little mess if you are using the regular coffee filter instead of pods but not too bad for the money.'),
(1582, 3, 1, 3, '2015-02-15', 'A bit complicated to operate WITHOUT reading the instructions. ... A bit complicated to operate WITHOUT reading the instructions. Once this is done it\'s OK. However, when plugged in, with a very short cord, it \"hums\" to the sound of \"your electric bill is escalating by the minute.\" We no unplug the very short cord when not in use.'),
(1583, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'Five Stars actually toasts unlike so many toaster ovens out there!'),
(1584, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-25', 'Looks and works great. Very Just opened it and used it. Looks and works great. Very happy'),
(1585, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-22', 'Five Stars Great product & Value'),
(1586, 10, 1, 4, '2016-01-13', 'Works great, I use mine a few times a week Works great, I use mine a few times a week for the normal smoothie. Sometimes it will run but not push anything around but all I need to do is shake the contents a bit before it\'s all good. I use Chia seeds and sometimes they get stuck in the bottom by the blades so that\'s annoying but otherwise GREAT BLENDER!'),
(1587, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-26', 'Five Stars sure does chew up stuff like a $100 blender, not $15'),
(1588, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-08', 'I was travelling and brought this to make fruit smoothies ... I was travelling and brought this to make fruit smoothies for my son.  Was wonderf when it worked but broke the 3 rd time I tried it:( . I now have to get another one'),
(1589, 4, 1, 1, '2015-10-23', 'One Star This is a terrible toaster oven'),
(1590, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-03', 'makes good coffee. Maybe could be a little hotter water ... Everything I hoped for. makes good coffee. Maybe could be a little hotter water temps when brewing.'),
(1591, 2, 1, 1, '2015-06-14', 'Burns toast. Looks bad We hate it. Burns every time you put a toast in at the lowest setting. Dials are huge and just looks out dated. If we kept the box I would have returned it.'),
(1592, 12, 1, 5, '2014-06-16', 'Great 50ish Toaster Very nice, you can graduate your toast preferences and you can have your toast ready in 1 minute if you want to. It\'s great and it\'s beautiful, retro style-looking.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1593, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-07', 'Great Upgraded Brewer I was very happy to get this Keurig (K250) as I wanted a replacement for another coffeemaker. I have a Keurig mini that works well, but this brewer is a definite upgrade from that. Unlike my mini version, you don\'t have to refill the water after each cup. This brewer has a large water reservoir that will last me all day long. It\'s extremely easy to use. Just fill the water in the reservoir and wait a couple of minutes for the water to preheat. Then, add your choice of K-cup, select the number of ounces from the touch screen then press the brew button. Unlike the mini version, as soon as you press the brew button, the coffee is instantly brewed in about 15 seconds. It\'s quick and easy to use and a definite upgrade from the mini version. The only drawback, however, is that not all of my k-cups were functional in this new brewer. So, if you have an older mini version or another Keurig, I would suggest keeping it as a backup brewer just in case not all of the k-cups are functional. Also, it would have been nice to have had a carafe, but it is not included with this particular model. Overall, this brewer is really fast and easy to use. It\'s sleek and functional and doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space. It\'s definitely recommended as an upgrade or a replacement brewer.'),
(1594, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-25', 'Just what I was looking for This is a great no frills product, it makes coffee, that\'s it. I use this pot daily, connected to my solar power system. I get 3 mugs of coffee without draining my battery bank. Another good feature is that when its off, it is really off. It doesn\'t have a clock or other bells and whistles using power when the appliance is not in use. Besides I already have a clock on the stove, the microwave and 1 on the wall, I don\'t need another. I am very pleased with this purchase'),
(1595, 5, 1, 3, '2017-01-07', 'No automatic shutoff valve It makes coffee. The lack of an automatic shutoff valve is annoying though.'),
(1596, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-19', 'Great Toaster...TOAST!!! After more than a year, my wife and family love this toaster.  The settings are great for everything we need.  You can\'t go wrong with Cuisinart.'),
(1597, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-21', 'This coffee pot is horrible. Followed the cleaning instructions before using it and ... This coffee pot is horrible.  Followed the cleaning instructions before using it and after brewing the coffee for the first time, all the grounds were in the coffee pot and it did not brew the amount of coffee per water (we make 10 cups each time and it would only brew 6 cups).  Tried using this for 2 weeks, cleaned it several more times, and the result was the same every single time.  This was an absolute waste of money.  Unfortunately, the day after we purchased this, the box was thrown out, so cannot return it.'),
(1598, 10, 1, 3, '2016-01-15', 'Three Stars Good value for the money.'),
(1599, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-23', 'I love this coffee pot I love this coffee pot, no pouring water in the top, or even lifting the top at all. Basket swings out to fill & empty and the base is on rollers so easily moves to wherever you want! This will be the only coffee pot I will by from now on!'),
(1600, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'Great coffee pot Great coffee pot.  I love the idea of being able to make 1 cup of coffee.  It\'s fast efficient and inexpensive.'),
(1601, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-03', 'Orange is the new Black Love the color.  Wish the reservoir was larger and ability to always be on 10 oz so didnt have to change it for each cup.  Otherwise good purchase.'),
(1602, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-19', 'First time I had such a good toaster. No more burnt toast. First time I had such a good toaster.'),
(1603, 11, 1, 1, '2014-07-27', 'Toasted things way too fast, so everything was always ... Toasted things way too fast, so everything was always burning. Then a piece of bread went on fire. Seems dangerous. I will replace with something higher-end.'),
(1604, 7, 3, 1, '2015-09-27', 'We bought the first one from Walmart some six months ago and from the beginning it was very slow to brew a pot of coffee then it just died. I contacted Hamilton Beach and they sent me a warranty replacement and I had to pay for the freight. It arrived some two weeks after they debited my VISA and worked fine for all of 9 days! Then it showed an error code... which is not in their manual and it\'s just \"locked up\". So... I look at the reviews of this thing and have to wonder how anyone could give this pile of junk anything but the lowest rating possible? I\'ll be calling the manufacturer again tomorrow morning and expect to hear nothing more than the usual apologies and more patronizing which will do nothing more than irritate me. So... if you want a reliable coffee maker... do not buy this one no matter what the price!'),
(1605, 5, 1, 1, '2014-12-23', 'Good coffee,  poor durability After searching for a week we selected this coffee pot. It is easy to use and makes a great cup of coffee. However after a little over a year it stopped working. Needless to say we would never purchase another Hamilton Beach coffee pot.'),
(1606, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Great choice I love this toaster.  I have had many toasters over the years and this one is far better than any others I have used.  I like that it has many degrees of settings so you can get just the right amount of browning that you want.  The features for bagels, defrosting and reheating are a great bonus.  You can even cancel during the toasting and select another degree of browning if you wish.  The Cuisinart brand is always good.  This one is exceptional. [[ASIN:B009GQ034C Cuisinart CPT-122 Compact 2-Slice Toaster]'),
(1607, 5, 1, 4, '2015-12-25', 'Great, simple easy to use coffee maker I like this coffee maker. The water reservoir comes off for easy filling and it looks good. It has mid level functionality, which is great. We had an expensive coffee maker prior to this and it was a pain in the butt. When this one goes out, I\'m getting another one.'),
(1608, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'We\'re happy with everything about it finally a towaster oven that toasts in a reasonably quick time. We\'re happy with everything about it.'),
(1609, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-13', 'Great Product This toaster oven is a great value. Amazing price, I use it for toasting, cooking and even warming food. Highly reccommend!'),
(1610, 11, 1, 5, '2015-07-11', 'This Works Very well Works very well and gets Nice & Hot as expected!'),
(1611, 10, 1, 5, '2016-08-07', 'Great personal sized blender at a great price Great personal sized blender at a great price. It does the same as the higher priced $100 ones. Easy to put together, easy to clean and doesnt take up alot of space. I keep one at home for my morning smoothies and one at the office for a smoothie before i go to the gym. Do yourself a favor and get this blender instead of the higher priced ones.'),
(1612, 4, 1, 5, '2016-07-02', 'Five Stars I really like the Cuisinart toaster owner.  I only wish it had a build in timer.'),
(1613, 2, 1, 2, '2015-05-26', 'Two Stars Took longer than my oven to cook small bites and toast.'),
(1614, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-02', 'Does what I need it for. Brews my coffee ... Does what I need it for. Brews my coffee in about 3 minutes. Not sure why anyone would need anything else.'),
(1615, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-02', 'No Spillage! It doesn\'t drip or dribble pouring a cup of coffee. IT DOES NOT DRIP OR DRIBBLE! You can pour fast or slow, will not spill. Has many other great features I just can\'t get over the previously mentioned one. Works great!'),
(1616, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-29', 'Five Stars Perfect.'),
(1617, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-20', 'I like it very much As what I read! I like it very much!'),
(1618, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-09', 'Five Stars works great'),
(1619, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-05', 'Five Stars great'),
(1620, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-07', 'Five Stars perfect for small applications'),
(1621, 2, 1, 3, '2015-11-18', 'Takes a while to heat up...just okay We had an older Black and Decker four-slice toaster oven that we loved, but finally died on us. We bought this as a replacement. It works fine, but takes a bit of time to heat up when using the bake feature, which we are not accustomed to. As such, we have to allow for extra cooking time, which is not always feasible, causing frustration. We don\'t want to pay return shipping, otherwise, we would likely return it and order a different toaster oven. If you are often able to allow for extra baking time, this toaster oven works fine.'),
(1622, 2, 1, 2, '2015-12-02', 'Be careful and make sure it\'s shut off. Sometimes it stays on when I don\'t mean it to. It\'s user error for sure, but the buttons are designed such that it\'s hard to tell when it\'s OFF and when it\'s in the \"stay on always\" mode.'),
(1623, 4, 1, 5, '2016-07-10', 'Five Stars Great replacement for the toaster oven that just broke. Got here pretty quick too.'),
(1624, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-27', 'Perfect toaster oven! This is my favorite toaster oven I\'ve had yet! You can control temperature, time, and choose heat source (top, bottom, both). The only thing I don\'t like is once you set the time, you can\'t stop it...you just have to wait til it\'s done. But you can turn the temperature off so as to not waste energy.'),
(1625, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-10', 'Well worth the price Was not happy with the price of this unit when I purchased, but wanted a good product. After buying and using it, I feel much better about what I paid. This is a well though out device. Worth the price if you drink lots of coffee. My only wish is that they had a way to turn the warmer temp down. I like my coffee at a bit cooler temp than this keeps it at so I have to either add ice or water to my coffee to get the temp down.'),
(1626, 9, 1, 1, '2016-01-13', 'Coffee is brewed cold. Very bad product I would like to return. The coffee is brewed so cold I have to heat it up in microwave. Please send return label.'),
(1627, 4, 1, 2, '2015-12-26', 'While I love the toaster Second one I ordered. While I love the toaster, the heating rod on two I have owned ended up welded to the floor of the toaster, risking a fire or worse. Only after a few yeas.'),
(1628, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-03', 'It is refreshing to find honesty and customer service like this! Great coffee maker for a great price!'),
(1629, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'Is it that to make a toaster that works? Finaly, a toaster that makes great toast! I\'ve wondered just how hard it must be to JUST do toast? I\'ve tried three or four different brands and ALL burned or under toasted the toast! This one is compact , good looking and JUST WORKS!!'),
(1630, 9, 1, 4, '2015-11-13', 'Four Stars I love the coffee maker. It makes restaurant style coffee!!'),
(1631, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-08', 'Don\'t buy if you travel/live in Europe Doesn\'t work anywhere in Europe because of different power outlet and power requirements. Very, very disappointed'),
(1632, 6, 1, 2, '2016-03-18', 'Not a good toaster! Bought for a gift but it did not evenly toast both sides. Sent it back.'),
(1633, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-29', 'This is a very nice small oven This is a very nice small oven.  It toasts, bakes, broils and has special settings for pizza, frozen snacks, potatoes and cookies.  I use it all the time instead of using my regular oven.  It comes with a nice sized pan but a regular sized cake pan will fit in it.'),
(1634, 1, 1, 2, '2016-04-20', 'Beware of older K-cup singles Little did I know, all single K-cups by Keurig do not work in this coffeepot.  I was replacing an older model and had many K-cups left from before.  This model does not read them.  They have to have been purchased after the manufacture of this particular System.  Even though mine were purchased directly from Keurig.'),
(1635, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-07', 'Five Stars Great product, easy to use.'),
(1636, 4, 1, 5, '2016-12-06', 'Five Stars Great toaster.'),
(1637, 9, 1, 1, '2016-01-17', 'I wanted to love it. First thing out of the box I ... I read all the reviews and decided on this coffee maker. I wanted to love it. First thing out of the box I realized I needed an extension cord to plug it in. I read it had a short cord but I put it right up against the wall with the outlet and still it is just not long enough to plug in. But I still wanted to love it, so I tried to hide the extension and started making coffee. I loved it for a whole month, until I brewed a full \"tank\" of coffee for guests and the coffee maker wouldn\'t stop pouring after the first person released the lever; we stood there with a pot under the machine to keep it from spilling on the floor; the next day we tried again but the coffee just poured out as it was brewing. I\'m trying to find a box big enough to return it in.'),
(1638, 7, 3, 5, '2016-06-02', 'It\'s great'),
(1639, 5, 1, 5, '2014-05-19', 'Small Space Saver We love this coffee maker as we have a small space and hated pulling our old coffee maker all the way out every time we made coffee. We have no leaks and no issues, love this!'),
(1640, 12, 1, 5, '2016-10-13', 'nice idea works nice  idea  works well.'),
(1641, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Kitchens New Toy Bought this for my girlfriend\'s birthday and surely surprised her big. Never used a coffee machine or even one of these infamous keurig everyone seems to be all hyped about. When she opened it and had me help her I was kind of surprised myself to see that it\'s very simple to put together and use. Within ten minutes we were making coffee, hot coco and even using the hot water function for an instant soup. I say not bad at all and can see why anyone buys a Keurig. Amazon is still king in its fast deliveries. Thank you.'),
(1642, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-14', 'Efficient with a minor inconvenience. Toasts well and is good at warming up muffins and pizza slices.  Turning on the toast function, which is what I use most,  requires turning the lower knob clockwise to activate the timer,  and then counter-clockwise to set the toast darkness desired. Seems like a built-in unnecessary step. Would be more efficient if you could just leave the darkness setting where you wanted it and just set timer.  Otherwise, an efficient toaster oven.'),
(1643, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-14', 'Five Stars ___'),
(1644, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'BEST Toaster Oven! I love this toaster oven! My KitchenAid oven finally broke after about 5 years. The switch broke and instead of selling a replacement part, KitchenAid told me I had to buy a whole new oven! Needless to say, I wanted to try a different brand. I found this oven and it was a good price so I bought it. When I brought it home and started using it I realized this is the BEST oven I have ever owned! It heats up quickly and the buttons make it really easy to program. It seems heavy duty and the crumb tray is easy to clean. I really love the quality and am excited to have it in my home. I hardly use my big oven because this little one works so well and is big enough to fit a lot! I\'m very happy with my purchase!'),
(1645, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-21', 'black & decker This is my third appliance from Black & Decker and I really like the quality of their appliances. The materials that they used are really high-quality. I\'ve been using it for months but I haven\'t had any complaints about it. I also like the buttons. I\'m not that sure if the process of using it is good because I am not the one who usually use it. My wife does so I\'m not that familiar with it.'),
(1646, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-14', 'Five Stars great sturdy producct.'),
(1647, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'Five Stars Great for one person. Works good and so convenient.'),
(1648, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Best coffee maker I have ever had! i love this coffee maker, I really like the design and look of it. It makes coffee really fast and I like the option of pulling out the water holder (?) to fill it up or just using the coffee pot to put the water in it. I really like the keep warm feature so it doesn\'t scorch the coffee and the programming feature is awesome!'),
(1649, 1, 1, 3, '2016-09-15', 'Three Stars Good product but it wasn\'t white at all, it beige/pearl...not quite what I wanted, but it will do.'),
(1650, 8, 1, 1, '2016-05-11', 'One Star Carafe is too thin and breaks easily.'),
(1651, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-05', 'Excellent for the price! Honestly, for what little money I paid, this toaster is an outstanding value. Only rated 4/5 because if you are looking for a toaster with more extensive features, you maybe need to look elsewhere. But if you want a cheap toaster that gets the job done, this one is perfect. Only complaint is that the capacity seems a bit small. Really need to squeeze four pieces of bread in.'),
(1652, 6, 1, 5, '2016-04-24', 'Five Stars Great toaster.'),
(1653, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-21', 'nice short cut to oven works great I\'m use it all the time and it does great'),
(1654, 10, 1, 4, '2016-06-21', 'Bought for a friend I only bought this for a friend to test out if I would get it but I got a big blender for my wedding but my friend was pleased.'),
(1655, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-25', 'Keurig 2.0 to replace 1st gen Keurig We got this Keurig 2.0 to replace our original Keurig that had an internal leak. The 2.0 system isn\'t as bad as it sounds - it does offer for more/smarter brew options depending on the type of K-Cup that\'s inserted. It also has a filter reminder option and the machine will tell you when it needs descaled. The only issue we\'ve had so far is that the unit won\'t power off for some reason. When you tap the power button on the bottom right hand corner, the unit will turn on, but it will not turn off. You have to unplug it from the wall and plug it back in. I have not contacted Keurig support about this, yet. The Keurig makes coffee that is about 60-70% as good as my pourover coffee with fresh, locally roasted beans. The convenience sometimes outweighs the hassle of heating up the kettle, grinding beans, etc. If I have the time, I\'ll always choose a pourover. This is nice to have, though. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1656, 6, 1, 1, '2016-08-01', 'Looks better than it performed The lever to lower the bread has a cheap feel to it. Suspect it won\'t last long. Toaster oven would have been a better choice.'),
(1657, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-10', 'Great Features Make it So Easy to Use! I rarely write reviews, but I must say that I do love this coffee maker!  I bought it as a replacement when my old one (a Mr. Coffee) stopped working after only two years!  This coffee maker is easy to use, and looks great on the counter.  I love the reservoir that pulls out and the easy open, front loaded filter.  I often feel like I have forgotten to do something before I turn it on (I haven\'t - it\'s simply that easy to get ready). The only thing I cannot attest to is how long it lasts; but with a Hamilton Beach product, I have high hopes that it will do well. Great coffee maker.  Great features.  Makes great coffee!'),
(1658, 9, 1, 2, '2016-08-16', 'For such a good brand and the price I was hoping we could ... Purchased in March.  For the last month or so when you push the lever to get the coffee it does not close and continues to pour.  Have the box and everything but return date has expired.  For such a good brand and the price I was hoping we could get it replaced.  Cannot use as  you have to either stand there and keep putting cups to catch the coffee or dump the coffee out of the retaining container which wastes the coffee.  Not happy:(.'),
(1659, 7, 3, 1, '2016-01-26', 'WISH I COULD HAVE CHECKED IT OUT FIRST.'),
(1660, 12, 1, 4, '2016-08-23', 'Four Stars So far, it\'s what I expected.'),
(1661, 3, 1, 3, '2016-01-09', 'I would have liked to have a button to just push it on It takes a little time to get use to it from my previous one. This one is a step up.  Honestly speaking, I would have liked to have a button to just push it on, and then put in the temperature I want. This one has predetermined temperatures which starts up very high, and then you have to bring it down, and it only goes 5 degrees at a time.  Very time consuming when you are in a hurry.  When I use this, I am usually in a hurry.'),
(1662, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-12', 'It had a good description on the page This is exactly what I wanted.  It had a good description on the page.  Compact, so easy to fill with a removable reservoir. Easy access to fill the coffee.  It just pops open right in the front and the different temps to stay warn. And best of all it has a brewing strength and I\'m using less coffee without sacrificing taste.  Other models  with the same features were twice the price.  This is a  great buy!.'),
(1663, 11, 1, 5, '2015-01-14', 'i love my toaster oven use it every day and still ... i love my toaster  oven use it every day and still works like new'),
(1664, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-29', 'Burning smell. Very disappointed. Every time I turn it on, it smokes.  Smells of burning plastic and I can actually see wisps of smoke coming out of it when it\'s empty and on. I\'ve read that this happens, perhaps it\'s shoddy construction, but I\'d rather not have to run it and smell the fumes for an hour or more before it is usable.  Unfortunately, that does appear to be my best option. I didn\'t realize this until after the return period was over (does anybody expect to buy a toaster that inappropriately smokes?) because I bought it and then didn\'t use it.  Going to run it for awhile and hope whatever it is burns off without giving me any sort of lung problems from inhaling the fumes.'),
(1665, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-27', 'Love this coffee pot Love this coffee pot.....the glass pot is recessed so it cannot be bumped or damaged. The neat square shape to the unit allows it to fit neatly on the counter.'),
(1666, 11, 1, 4, '2015-09-17', 'It has been easy to use and I like how a bake pan ... The settings for toasting is a bit off, but once you get used to it you will get the timing right. I\'ve made small meals in this and I use it daily to make toasted sandwiches. I warm tortillas and naan with this. I\'ve even cooked salmon and vegetables in this as well. It has been easy to use and I like how a bake pan is included with it. Pro-tip: wrap the bake pan with foil before use for easy clean up and to keep the pan free from burns and accumulating food particles (it is not non-stick)'),
(1667, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Five Stars Great product for the money.'),
(1668, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'Five Stars Very good_'),
(1669, 11, 1, 3, '2015-01-23', 'Three Stars doesn\'t get to the proper temerature'),
(1670, 12, 1, 3, '2016-04-12', 'It\'ll toast your bread but the compartment for baking stinks ... It\'ll toast your bread but the compartment for baking stinks if you axe me. Nachos, no.  Chicken parm sandwich reheated, no.  1 Slice of pizza, maybe.'),
(1671, 8, 1, 2, '2015-05-09', 'So far YUCK Makes weak coffee at best and I like it to pour itself and walk over to me. But call it what you will it makes great tea and I like that strong as well. Better yet I can do lose leaf tea too just use a paper filter.....as for coffee it\'s back to the perkalator'),
(1672, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-07', 'Four Stars perfect small system for our camper.'),
(1673, 11, 1, 5, '2014-05-26', 'Time to UPgrade The Kitchen appliances are never a big subject to chat about. When it takes forever to heat an item when it will wilt in the microwave and ONLY a Toaster oven will do. this is So well designed the knobs are easy to read and use. The heating is quick and It does EVERYTHING is claims and more. the price was great shipped fast and I am going to get one more as a gift'),
(1674, 12, 1, 5, '2014-01-15', 'Toaster This is exactly what I have been looking for ! The red color looks great in my kitchen and the toast / broil combo is perfect.'),
(1675, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Perfect Perfect'),
(1676, 12, 1, 4, '2016-08-03', 'Four Stars Perfect for the r.v. Too.'),
(1677, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-17', 'Dear NC State -- please fix the typo found at http://poole.ncsu.edu/undergraduate/global/alexander-hamilton-scholars/ The Alexander Hamilton Scholars Program is a dual degree program at North Carolina State University in which students earn a degree from both the Poole College of Management and the College of Humanities and Social Sciences. Hamilton Scholars are a select group of highly motivated students who wish to have a career in the international business world. Hamilton Scholars is primarily an academic program in which the participants focus on completing all of the requirements for the two different degrees. However, the program also provides student activities outside the classroom. Hamilton Scholars complete a major in Accounting, Business Administration or Economics within the Poole College of Management, whilst also pursuing an additional Bachelor of Arts degree in International Studies within the College of Humanities and Social Sciences. Hamilton Scholars expand their knowledge in a ****foriegn**** language and continue to pursue their international interests with a study abroad program. The purpose of the dual degree program is to produce well rounded business professionals who are knowledgeable about international issues and have skills to function successfully in cross cultural settings.  In an ever-increasing global economy and interconnected business world, Hamilton Scholar graduates emerge as highly qualified and competitive individuals.'),
(1678, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-13', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(1679, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-19', 'Looking good Keurig is always good. This particular one is very attractive.'),
(1680, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-04', 'Five Stars I love it. It has excellent features. For instance, the water is added with a removable container on the back of the unit and it is not necessary to pour water into the top. The filter compartment swings open even if the pot is in place and the filter holder easily lifts out so I can carry the whole thing to the trash can to dump the old filter. The digital controls are easy and intuitive. There is a \"bold\" setting for stronger coffee. It is the best coffee maker I have owned in a long time.'),
(1681, 4, 1, 2, '2016-01-03', 'Chinese kitchens do not have ovens,so there is no \'best selling china made toaster oven\' I just bought this because the current Black and Decker models have only 3 inches clearance between the tray and the top heating element: all my older ones had 3 and 1/2 inches clearance. However I shall not even be opening the box because I have read these reviews, and I believe them. Since these ALL seem to be made with parts from China, I googled \'\'How unusual is it for an apartment or house to have an oven in China?\'\' Being based on rice, Chinese cuisine has not historically relied on the CONCEPT OF BAKING...... therefore their cooking involves boiling, steaming or frying. The answer is that the Chinese tend to use microwave ovens today, but have no use for a \'toaster oven\' OR....a \'big oven\'/range/cooking stove .....apparently these are almost totally non existent in Chinese kitchens.'),
(1682, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-17', 'Five Stars Works very well and looks good in my new kitchen.'),
(1683, 12, 1, 5, '2015-10-13', 'NAM! there is no timer so SET ONE- do NOT pretend to remember something in 2 minutes! this baby cooks fast.  But as long as you don\'t burn anything its is perfect - fast , simple, and good looking in the kitchen which is hard to achieve'),
(1684, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'A Great Oven I have had zero problems with this oven.  I wish I had followed my first mind to buy a convection over years ago.  It cooks everything quickly and easily.  There\'s no mess with it.  I was worried that it would get too hot, or smell up the house like in other reviews, or burn the food.  But, it cooks everything just right.  It\'s much better than my traditional oven.'),
(1685, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-26', 'Does not blend well This blender does not pull down fruit and ice to the blades at all.  Bottom section blended, top not at all.'),
(1686, 11, 1, 1, '2014-11-30', 'One Star Way to small! I am unable to fit an 8 x 8 roasting pan I it. Really small.'),
(1687, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-16', 'Great toaster oven This Black & Decker toaster oven is and excellent value for the money. It is everything I was looking for in a toaster oven. It\'s compact size is perfect for someone with limited counter space. It does a great job on toast, once you get the settings figured out. Burned a couple before I found the one I liked. Hint, stay on the low side to keep from burning your toast. Bakes very well. The temps on the dial seem accurate. I would recommend this toaster oven for anyone looking for a inexpensive one that works well.'),
(1688, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-24', 'very poorly made Died after 1 use, spend a little more this is very poorly made'),
(1689, 8, 1, 3, '2016-02-09', 'I got this coffee maker for me and my husband ... I got this coffee maker for me and my husband. We normally have just a cup of coffee every day. I go the coffee maker on August and stopped working by end of January which is 6 months which I  think its OK for 13 dollar machine. Size was small as it says 5 cup may by only 8 oz cups they mean because for regular coffee mug when is full gives you may be 3 cups only.'),
(1690, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-13', 'I like the look of this toaster oven and using it ... I like the look of this toaster oven and using it is easy. One thing I don\'t like about it, is that when using the bake setting, the oven does not signal when the preferred temp is reached. On my last toaster oven the temperature light turned off when the preferred baking temp was reached. This is guess work. Other than that it\'s a good buy.'),
(1691, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-23', 'Works great!! The size is just perfect for a ... I\'ve been using it for more than a year now. Works great!! The size is just perfect for a glass of banana cashew smoothie.'),
(1692, 6, 1, 4, '2015-07-25', 'I like it but.... I reallyl like the toaster but just wish it made sound when the toast pops up!!!'),
(1693, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Five Stars My wife loves it.'),
(1694, 4, 1, 3, '2016-05-10', 'Three Stars Worked fine for about 1 1/2 years. Great. Then bottom rod split open and started bowing up. Done.'),
(1695, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'Nice product This machines prepares my breakfast everyday. I make my protein shake smoothie and take it with me to work sometimes.'),
(1696, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', '... the Keurig to replace an old coffe maker and love it! I would recommend everyone to buying it ... I bought the Keurig to replace an old coffe maker and love it! I would recommend everyone to buying it verses regular coffee makers .,,.Love it!'),
(1697, 4, 1, 3, '2015-06-08', 'This was not a bargain oven and it seems after ... This was not a bargain oven and it seems after a year or so the element has lost a lot of its life.  That is, it takes longer to cook the same foods than before.'),
(1698, 4, 1, 1, '2016-07-12', 'Terrible Product! The worse product ever! If possible, I would rate it negative stars. I was excited to get this at first and not even 2 years later, the heating element started to bend out of shape. It burns all my toast and I cannot use the bottom rack because the heating element is in the way. I cannot even use it as a broiler. So needless to say, it is a useless product.  I complained to Cuisinart and it\'s been weeks and have not heard back from them. I don\'t think they care about their customers. With that said, I will NEVER BUY ANYTHING CUISINART EVER AGAIN. Poor product and poor customer service.'),
(1699, 12, 1, 4, '2014-01-17', '2 for 1 It was time to buy a new toaster, I found this that is both a toaster and a mini oven so that was great. Saves me counter space in the kitchen which is also good because I dont have a very big one. It works great and heats up fast so dont walk away from it your first time using it.'),
(1700, 5, 1, 1, '2015-05-09', 'Stay away! Piece of junk.'),
(1701, 7, 3, 1, '2016-12-02', 'I ordered this as a Christmas gift. I get the coffee maker in the mail. It had a sticker on the side that it had one owner with a date from May. No where in the description did it tell me that it was used. Very upset about this purchase.'),
(1702, 5, 1, 3, '2016-06-20', 'The stainless part where the power and other buttons comes ... The stainless part where the power and other buttons comes off when you swing the basket out to put in coffee or empty basket.'),
(1703, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-05', 'Really love many features of it I\'ve had this machine now for about 2 weeks. Really love many features of it.  The water reservoir is on the back of the machine and lifts out so that you can easily fill it.  The machine itself slides and swivels easily to make it easy to pull it out from under your cabinets and turn it around to access the reservoir...love that.  The carafe has a hinged lid so it also is very easy to deal with. And the whole thing makes a very decent pot of coffee.  I think in my many years of owning coffee machines this is my favorite, hands down!'),
(1704, 1, 1, 4, '2016-09-23', 'I love it but I love it but, it does\'\'t recognize all Keurig cups. The smarter the machine the more annoying some times. Looks great though.'),
(1705, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-13', 'Great blender This is a really good personal blender. You can carry your smoothie around with you  because the container you blend it in is also your cut with a lid that has a tap on it you can close. I really like this, it works great. Percfect.'),
(1706, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-12', 'Five Stars Probably the best toaster oven I have ever had. Very even cooking, perfect pizza, perfect toast. easy to clean.'),
(1707, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Five Stars the coffee maker is the best I have ever owned but I was over charged $12.00 for it.'),
(1708, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-28', 'I love this machine I love this machine! Its has replaced our old machine and this one is so much easier to use and makes the drink in less than half the time.  Im very happy with this product and encourage this product to all who loves coffee and teas.  My 10 year old makes teas from this everyday and loves it and is very simple for her to use.  Its a very easy clean up and non messy.  The only downfall that i have would be that the coffees and teas are a little pricey but its well worth the taste and many variety\'s that they have out and they are constantly coming out with more flavors to love. I would buy this all over again!! Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review'),
(1709, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'Great Little Oven Absolutely LOVE this device.  In my home, I cook for 2.  I hardly use the big oven anymore.  Terrific for Bagel Bites or pizza rolls on movie night.  My wife has also baked cookies in it, and they came out great.  I don\'t find it hard to clean at all.'),
(1710, 11, 1, 3, '2014-04-11', 'Toasting is a bit cumbersome I had a Black and Decker toaster oven in the past. It worked great but was beginning to look a little ratty (had for about 10 years). So I purchased this one. It looks very nice on my counter. It takes a little getting used to figuring out how not to burn the toast edges - you have to turn the knob past a certain point and then back down to the darkness of the toast you want. I\'ve had this oven for about a month and I still sometimes burn them. Also, my last one would automatically shut off when I opened the door. This one doesn\'t and more than once I\'ve found it still burning brightly when I\'m well done using it. Aside from these issues, I basically happy with it. I do like the removable bottom tray that allows for easy cleaning of the oven. It would help if Black & Decker would bring back some of the older features to make use of the product a little easier.'),
(1711, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-31', 'my wife liked it, I Well , my wife liked it, I liked'),
(1712, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-02', 'Great Toaster! Cuisnart still makes the best Great Toaster!  Cuisnart still makes the best.  Would buy again.'),
(1713, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-01', 'love it Great buy bagels defrosting glad I bought it purchase it. it\'s worth every penny! Cuisinart products are always delivering in price & quality.'),
(1714, 2, 1, 2, '2016-01-29', 'Poorly designed We have tried the baking, broiling, and toasting functions_.it takes operation of all three dials to do any one of these functions.  The dials are hard to read_small black print on silver background.  You need good light to see what you are doing.  The exterior gets hot with no way to grasp it to move it without pot holders.  There are no handles on the sides.  Even when cool one must be careful not to drop it as the sides are slick. This is the third B&D toaster oven we have had over the past 20+ years so thought this one would be a great choice.  So sorry it is no longer a well designed unit. As for toasting, baking, and broiling, it works fine so if you don\'t mind these other problems, you will probably like it.  Me...I am returning it.'),
(1715, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-15', 'Tosteroven Great toster oven just what I needed'),
(1716, 2, 1, 3, '2016-03-19', 'If you can afford it buy better it\'s cheap cause its cheap This is what it is you get what you pay for situations it\'s more wood than it seems it really doesn\'t fit four pieces of bread that\'s a lie does heat up pretty well fits nicely if you don\'t have much counter space but the non stick pan you can leave off the non'),
(1717, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-02', 'Works as advertised. I just wish there was room ... Works as advertised.  I just wish there was room for them to have printed larger letters or icons.  I have an enlargement of the dials tacked to the wall above to help adjust the dials correctly.'),
(1718, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Highly recommended! We love this coffee maker. The flavor is very good, the water is hot enough, and the \"bold\" setting is great. It\'s easy enough to clean, and the plastic rim around the glass carafe is a huge asset. We had a cheaper model Hamilton Beach coffee maker that brewed really inadequate coffee, and I was so afraid I was going to shatter the pot! It\'s worth paying a little more for this model!.'),
(1719, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-16', 'No overflows Yes it passed the test. No spills, easy access n my husband says it provides good tasting coffee! Thanks'),
(1720, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'Very Pleased with our New Coffee Maker I picked this up to replace a Mr. Coffee coffee-maker that I\'d been using for almost 10 years. I read good reviews of this model and decided to try it. This is a great coffee-maker. Pros: The removable water reserve is awesome - it really allows you to fill it up where you want to (sink, etc.) and it allows you to easily and gently clean it by hand. No more mysterious and murky water reserve. The programming is dependable and easy. It makes coffee each morning without any hassles. Cons: Haven\'t found one yet'),
(1721, 5, 1, 3, '2015-03-03', 'Pretty Good, not hot enough This is very nice.  Works great, makes good coffee, has program option which i like, I also like the 4 cup brewing option.  It has a selection of heat levels for the burner, which works great.  HOWEVER, when the coffee is first brewed, it is NOT as hot as I like it.  I don\'t like it scalding or anything, but I always have to nuke it, which annoys me.  If you let it sit on the burner it gets hotter.  But who wants to wait?  Overall, decent product.'),
(1722, 4, 1, 1, '2016-04-12', 'I always hated the beeping sound when the toast is ready - ... I always hated the beeping sound when the toast is ready - most annoying - but after about three years of owner ship, the front heating element has expanded and bent upwards so much that we can\'t even use the rack in the lower position. I think the elements in this model are generally faulty - so don\'t buy one!'),
(1723, 10, 1, 1, '2016-02-23', 'Worst blender I\'ve ever had Won\'t even blend smoothies. I can only use it to mix basic protein shakes. Worst blender I\'ve ever had.'),
(1724, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-20', 'Love this brewer! Love this brewer.  It is easy to use and so convenient for someone like me who doesn\'t have lots of time to wait for a pot of coffee to brew.  I really like that there are different cup size options and that a carafe can be brewed.  Only drawback is that older kcups won\'t work in this machine.  I received this product free to test, but after trying it would definitely recommend it!!'),
(1725, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-01', 'Love it I\'ve been pretty die-hard Cuisinart for many years, but cheated for a while with a Hamilton Beach BrewStation simply because I loved the idea of not having to deal with a carafe. I found the dispenser button to be a pretty awful design flaw though and couldn\'t wait to find something else to replace it. Cuisinart perfectly addresses that design flaw, as well as maintaining all the other features I\'ve always loved about their brewing products. I\'ve had this model nearly a month and have had exactly zero problems with it - and it gets used 2-3 times a day every single day. I have coffee twice a day every day with maybe a 3rd brew happening on the weekend. I haven\'t had any issues at all with the gauge, or leaking, or anything else. I wish it had temperature and brew strength settings like their other models, and perhaps a better warming system than the hot plate, but that\'s certainly not a deal breaker since I\'ve yet to experience burnt coffee. All in all, awesome.'),
(1726, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'Five Stars Works well for the right price'),
(1727, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'MY MORNING SAVIOUR! I love this one! As a healthcare industry worker, my hours are irregular compared to other people. I wake up at 5am ish and start the hot tub. Thanks to Keurig K200, I start my morning easily and get through with my day! Every night when I go to bed, I think about the coffee I\'d be smelling when I wake up. mmm!!! Compared to the old ones, the water heats up immediately and brewing doesn\'t take more than 2 minutes which is AMAZING! Also, the water filters come with them which are cool, as well. I received this product for free to test it out, so I can\'t complain! Trust me, you would NOT regret taking this one home with you :)'),
(1728, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-14', 'Five Stars I bought this for my mother and she loves it ,since she only drinks 2 cups a day.'),
(1729, 4, 1, 4, '2015-11-13', 'A kitchen helper WE all like it, simple to operate and care for.'),
(1730, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-04', 'Nice little toaster Works well though feels a bit flimsy. But good for the price.'),
(1731, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-04', 'Really good coffee and it\'s fun to use. First I must say I did not purchase from Amazon. I came to find a replacement water reservoir for the one I dropped (Amazon doesn\'t have one). With that out of the way...I have owned this maker for 13 months and we\'re very happy with it. Happy enough that rather than go out and find something new, I\'m willing to spend the $30 to replace the water reservoir I broke. There are some drawbacks/wishes, but they\'re very minimal and not enough to keep me from liking this machine enough to write a review. On the plus side: 1) In addition to making a very good cup of coffee, it\'s a lot of fun! When we\'re done having coffee we make a pot of hot water to keep for hot chocolate and other instant drinks, snacks, oatmeal, etc. 2) You have the option of making as much or as little as you like. 3) I can use paper filters so I don\'t have to deal with messy grounds. 4) It accommodates both tall and wide cups/bowls. 5) I originally thought the light on the dispenser and the gauge were a little gimmicky until I found how useful they really are. The gauge is not accurate but gives you a pretty good idea of what\'s left in the reservoir. 6) If your diligent, it\'s easy to clean (found that out the hard way). 7) Programmable...what\'s not to like about coffee being ready when you are? 8) Programmable Auto Shut-off up to 4 hours. 9) Fast. I haven\'t timed it but I never find myself standing in front of it wishing it would hurry! Now for the drawbacks/wishes: 1) I wish there was a separate power button for the hot plate. If you want to keep things hot for more than 4 hours you can only start another brew cycle. At the end of the day, this is a coffee maker and you should not keep coffee for 4 hours. That just tastes bad. But as I mentioned above we make hot water too and I worry that if I don\'t add water to the reservoir I may damage the machine. My issue, not the machines. 2) You will need some sort of rolling tray under it. While the machine will fit under a cabinet, there isn\'t enough space to open the lid and access the coffee basket and coffee reservoir. Not a big deal. From what I can tell most coffee makers are like that. 3) Even if you have the clearance, a tray of some sort is needed, especially if it\'s placed on a wooden counter. The drip tray is also designed to catch any liquid that gets under the coffee reservoir. It catches most but not all. Condensation forms on the lid and when you open it, that water slips right down between the machine and the reservoir. It really is minimal. I just keep mine on a plastic tray, wipe out any liquid I see when I remove the coffee reservoir (be careful if the hot plate is still hot) and occasionally have some dribbles to wipe up under the drip tray. 4) Ease of cleaning. This was a big problem but now is under control. Cuisinart says you can put the coffee reservoir in the top rack of a dishwasher. I can\'t speak to that. I have never tried to use the dishwasher. I use it too often through the day and run my dishwasher only when full. I made my coffee in the morning and then in the evening, when I was getting it ready for the next day, I hand washed all the parts in hot soapy water and even used a bottle brush. About 3 months ago we came up with the hot water idea and I noticed there were brown flecks floating in it. I realized these flecks were coffee residue and if it\'s floating in my water, it\'s floating in my coffee too!. I went crazy trying to clean this thing. But there are so many nooks and crannies inside the coffee reservoir that cannot be reached, even with a toothbrush. I thought about trying Dip-it (a fabulous percolator cleaner) but was afraid it might damage the plastic of the machine. Recognizing the machine was already no good if I couldn\'t properly clean it, I did a little Dip-it research and decided to try their soaking method. All I can say is EWWW! It looked like I brewed a pot of coffee but it worked like a dream and we haven\'t had a problem since! Now I\'m just very careful to wash the coffee reservoir IMMEDIATELY after I pour my last cup. I make sure the coffee doesn\'t get a chance to dry inside and I wash it the same way...really hot soapy water and a bottle brush. 3 months, Fleck-free! All and all one of the best little home coffee makers out there (IMHO). I see other reviewers had problems at the 2 year mark. Maybe I\'ll check in again when I hit it! Hope this helps. Enjoy your day!'),
(1732, 5, 1, 1, '2014-02-04', 'Totally dissapointed Upon arrival, I unpacked my product with joyous anticipation.  Then, THUD, the controls did not work, the water did not heat to brewing temperature and so I will not even get to try  what I was hoping would be a good cup of coffee.  Why, oh why, can such a simple product\'s working parts go so wrong.  This would be a fantastic product.  It is designed perfectly.  Now I have to try and repack and ship back.'),
(1733, 11, 1, 5, '2016-02-15', 'Good quality. I use it every day. Good quality.'),
(1734, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'so yummy and tastey really love it Love how quick and delicious the coffee is. I love how tastey and hot it comes out of the keurig and it doesnt waste any coffee like the other machines and the best part is that i got it for free to try out'),
(1735, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-04', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker.'),
(1736, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-16', 'love the color and it works well. Cute little single serve plastic blender'),
(1737, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-26', 'Liked mine so much I bought a red one for my mother I have been using this blender to make smoothies for a couple of months now and it is working great.  I didn\'t realize that I\'d need to hold the button to blend, but that is really not an issue.  It makes quick work of any frozen fruit I put into it.  Easy to clean and travels very well.  Fits right into my car\'s cup holder.  Love it!'),
(1738, 4, 1, 2, '2015-04-29', 'This was great until one day the heating element malfunctioned and caused ... This was great until one day the heating element malfunctioned and caused a potential dangerous situation. I was baking some chicken for lunch and immediately I noticed one of the heating elements not heating all the way through and a hot spot developed. It was glowing a bright white and was about to spark. This hotspot was about to ignite into a potential fire if I wasn\'t standing right there watching it. I\'ve had this product for about 3.5 years and it\'s sad that it\'s come to this.'),
(1739, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'Fantastic I purchased this Toastation two days ago, and couldn\'t be happier. It was getting really old having to toast bread in the oven at breakfast. This little toaster/toaster oven does a wonderful job in a shorter amount of time. I love how easy it is to clean the crumbs out. Definitely worth the money!!'),
(1740, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Life changer I\'ve been drinking coffee since I was 18 in the Navy. I\'m 40 now and I can say a lot of changes have been made in the way of coffee drinking. My wife just bought this product for me for Father\'s Day. Best present ever. I can\'t stop drinking coffee. It\'s changed my routine up in the morning but I won\'t be making any changes for years. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1741, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-08', '4.5 Stars, but it\'s a personal thing If I could give a \"4.5\" I would ... but just for minor flaws that are a personal thing. First, the carafe has plastic around the top edge ... I assume this is to help it not chip or break, which is GOOD, however there is always a little bit of coffee (or water when washing out) that gets stuck in the edge - see photo. Another thing that irks me just a little is the display is SUPER BRIGHT ... which might be really nice for some folks but I would prefer a dimming option. And one final thing - the water reservoir is kind of hard to see through when looking straight on. Now, that could just be the lighting in my house, I don\'t know. BUT I figured out a way around this: I just look inside the tank while filling and can see the marks on the other side, through the tank. I\'m not sure if that makes sense or not?! Again, these are minor things. We\'ve been using this coffee maker at least once a day for a few months now (ever since we got it) and like it a lot. I would recommend it to others.'),
(1742, 10, 1, 2, '2016-03-11', 'Two Stars Weak.'),
(1743, 9, 1, 4, '2015-06-08', 'This is a nice coffee maker This is a nice coffee maker.  It\'s quite easy to keep clean and makes and keeps the coffee hot.  The only problem I\'ve had with mine is it sometimes leaks - not because I fill it too much, it just does leak, but only a small amount of water and not all the time.  I looked at several different makes and models and choose this one and am glad I did.  I like it much better than a coffee maker with a cafe/pot, which is what I previously owned. You can make 10-12 cups or up to 4 cups depending on the setting you use. It is easily programmed to automatically make coffee and then shut off at set times. The shower head distributes the water in over the coffee grounds in the basket/filter - you can use filters or the permanent gold basket,  but not both at the same time - so I think you get a richer coffee flavor. Overall it\'s a good product and I highly recommend it.'),
(1744, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-02', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(1745, 5, 1, 3, '2015-10-10', 'Great, until... Bought this in March of 2014 and it was perfect! I even recommended it to my sister in law. Until....about 16 mos. later it just stopped working! It had power and the brew button lit up like it was working, but nothing happened. I was very sad about it. Sad to just put it in the trash can after loving it so much. Boo.'),
(1746, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-19', 'I love this. The best feature is the removable water ... I love this. The best feature is the removable water tank. No more spilling water and making trips back and forth to the sink. The unit itself is small and doesn\'t take up a lot of space on the counter. The other great selling feature is that this doesn\'t open from the top but rather pulls out from the front to fill with coffee, so I am not constantly having to pull this out from underneath the cabinets to open the lid.'),
(1747, 5, 1, 4, '2015-01-01', 'The Hamelton Beach has some nice features; the counter slide ability The Hamelton Beach has some nice features; the counter slide ability, the removable water compartment, brew adjustment, and heat adjustment, Most importantly, it makes a good cup of coffee. We have not had the leaking in the water fill issue that some have mentioned. I suspect it was not seated correctly. Maybe it wears after time. I just leave it in there. The fill is much more accessible than many I have seen. It is nice that you can remove it for cleaning. Some have mentioned the coffee is not kept hot enough. The hottest setting is fine for me. It is said too hot coffee hides the flavor. I think that is why some chains serve the coffee so hot. Then you can\'t tell it tastes bad. The one time I tried the bold brew setting I found the coffee weak. However I was using a coffee brand I don\'t normally use so I will update this later. All and all it is a good machine and would recommend it. We bought this because our Cuisinart coffee tea combo maker that we have had for several years started leaking water from the coffee fill into the tea fill thus crating stagnant water,'),
(1748, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-11', 'Best bang for the bucks. This coffee maker was purchased after a thorough review of reviews. It replaced a short line of other drip coffee makers which had all died after various years of service. I am a bit of a coffee nut, in that I purchase and grid my own beans and have a fair sense of what a good cup of coffee tastes like. This device, in my opinion, is the absolute best combination of features and pricing that you are apt to find.anywhere. The first maker that I received had its electronics die on the second pot that I made. This is not unusual; electronics either die immediately or they last forever. So I sent it back and in two days had another. (Great customer service, by the way!) Now to the coffee maker itself: The pot is great! No drip or spills when you pour from it. The reservoir is truly handy and easy to fill. Unlike many others which require you to pour a pot of water into them, this one lifts off for filling and has clearly marked volume lines. The filter basket is very easy to access as it swings out when you depress a release button and has is easily removed for cleaning. The electronics are easily programed for an automatic start at a future time and the manual start is as simple as pushing a button.  It has a pleasing appearance and is not particularly loud when it is running. This unit has an option to increase brewing time so that the coffee produced is changed from \"regular\" to \"bold\". It also has an adjustable \"keep warm\" feature which allows the brewed coffee to be held at any of three temps. You can also just turn it off if desired. In short, this is not the cheapest coffee maker you can find, but it is probably the best combination of features that you can find on a coffee maker and at a very good price level.'),
(1749, 7, 3, 2, '2015-12-09', 'The filter supplies does not work.Using less than the maximum allowed, it overflows and starts to build up along the top of the machine (you won\'t notice unless you look) Reusable k-cup filters don\'t fit Amount of coffee dispensed is inconsistent from 1 cup to the next even when using the exact same amount of grinds. Splatters coffee while brewing.'),
(1750, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Five Stars thanks so much....quick delivery'),
(1751, 3, 1, 5, '2014-03-10', 'The Best This is the best toaster oven I have ever owned.  It does exactly what a toaster oven should do.  It\'s dependable, large, and nice looking as far as toaster ovens go.  Can\'t go wrong with this one.'),
(1752, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'The removable water cistern is AWESOME! No more spilling water all over the place ... I\'ve had this for about 2 months now. The time setting feature is very convenient for waking up with fresh coffee! The removable water cistern is AWESOME! No more spilling water all over the place while trying to pour using the carafe. It has 3 different settings depending on how much coffee you want to make. I usually only make 2-4 \"cups\" in the morning, so this setting is nice!'),
(1753, 4, 1, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Good toaster oven. Good toaster oven.'),
(1754, 6, 1, 4, '2015-08-21', 'mmmmm,toast No toasting problems at all. Breads I use tend to be very sturdy, whole-grain and seems to work well for those.'),
(1755, 2, 1, 2, '2016-07-28', 'Looks sleek. But almost impossible to get settings right ... Looks sleek. But almost impossible to get settings right for toasting.  You end up with either burnt toast or untoasted bread.'),
(1756, 6, 1, 1, '2015-07-29', 'do your researchn 1st yep my fault did not read the comments the bagel control still toast both sides of bagel and it is as hot outside as inside complete waste of money toasters I had before toasted inside only...oh well buy another donate to charity'),
(1757, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Does a good job toasting at different levels Compact, seems to be well made. Does a good job toasting at different levels. Well satisfied.'),
(1758, 4, 1, 1, '2015-05-17', 'Cuisinart TOB 40 Surprised that it has no timer. You should disclose that. Even the cheapest toaster ovens have a timer and auto-off Very disappointed in that It does cook well but you have to stay and watch it.'),
(1759, 5, 1, 1, '2017-01-12', 'This was delivered on August 29th of 2016, and ... This was delivered on August 29th of 2016, and today, by Jan 11, 2017, it no longer works.  I didn\'t even work for 5 months.  When I turn it on, it gurgles and gurgles, but the water isn\'t \'perked\' from the reservoir into the pot.  After 30 minutes, no coffee.  I am purchasing another brand and would suggest buying the service plan.'),
(1760, 7, 3, 5, '2015-12-30', 'We have used 3 different brands of single serve coffee cups(Spartan, K-cups, Camerons) in this machine and it has worked great! Traditional brew works good as well. Everything we hoped for in a single serve machine. Functionality is a five star, we will have to wait and see about reliability as we have only been using it for 1 week.'),
(1761, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-05', 'and it works great powering through those ice cubes I use it for iced coffee bev, and it works great powering through those ice cubes.'),
(1762, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Five Stars This is really awesome and cheap!'),
(1763, 1, 1, 1, '2016-09-07', '... to say what\'s wrong with this thing and others like it. Costs well beyond it\'s worth I can\'t even begin to say what\'s wrong with this thing and others like it. Costs well beyond it\'s worth, bulky and inefficient. Hot water, being the key to a good cup of coffee, is non-existent here. Tepid to somewhat warm at best.  K Cups are the biggest marketing rip-off since the pet rock, which at LEAST caused amusement. Too many parts to deal with. We\'ve taken an extremely simple process and made it both complicated and expensive. I have since gone back to an electric percolator and the difference is astounding. I will never ever again own a coffee brewer more complicated than a percolator or a simple, basic brewer.  Add coffee, water, wait a few minutes,drink, dump the grinds, rinse out, have a nice day!.'),
(1764, 1, 1, 1, '2016-02-04', 'My first morning making my cup of coffee was not fun, I had to wait and wait for the ... I was in need of a new coffee maker, I was deciding between this model and the smaller model where you add water with each cup, but since my previous machine was add fresh water with each use i thought the reservoir would come in handy. First I was surprised that this didn\'t come with sample k cups. And since it will only let you brew their brand of cups i was lucky i had some. Most of my favorites are not Keurig specific. My first morning making my cup of coffee was not fun, I had to wait and wait for the water to heat up, i understand the water needs to get hot but heat according to the size ill be using. If i just want a cup, Im still waiting for the entire amount of water to heat. My first cup i drank was super weak. My second cup brewed quicker and I pressed the button to make it stronger. The second cup was fine, but after it was finished brewing I was told to add more water. Whats the point of having a reservoir if after only 2 cups i have to add more water. I will be putting this back in the box and returning it. Not happy at all. First world problems.'),
(1765, 4, 1, 4, '2015-07-12', 'really like the sleek look really like the sleek look. however it is on the bigger size compared to other toaster ovens. it might be because it also bakes and broils. love the easy clean pull out bottom tray! and the one button push for toast and bagel cooking!'),
(1766, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-02', 'Great product Good features and a reliable brand - makes predictably uniform toast every time.'),
(1767, 2, 1, 2, '2015-12-20', 'Unhappy I bought this mainly to use as an alternative to warming up my big oven for a baked potato or something small.  The oven heats up nicely but it does not stay on even tho\' I set the time to stay on.  I\'m very disappointed.'),
(1768, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-13', 'The tray that came with this doesn\'t fit. We ... The tray that came with this doesn\'t fit.  We contacted Black and Decker, but two months later we still haven\'t received the part, and are without a toaster!'),
(1769, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-26', 'hot stuff wonderful!  i love it;  can now make cheese sandwiches & toast ennglish muffins  it fits in nicely, &  looks good  . other folks in here have one just like it.  ty'),
(1770, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-10', 'Five Stars Everything i expected love the product super fast shipping'),
(1771, 6, 1, 4, '2015-01-20', 'This looks like the answer to the toaster quest! Gave this toaster four stars as have just started using it for about two weeks. it works far better than our previous unit and the \"cancel\" button that pops the toast up is great, no burned fingers and immediate release of toast is getting too brown. English muffins are still being experimented with but setting 4 seems pretty good so far. I wish the toaster sloped forward so the heat did not go directly up to our cabinet but I try to move it out when in use. Not sure when finding a good toaster got so difficult but it did and seems you pay lots for bad performance, I think Cuisinart is a great brand so we should enjoy this unit for many years.'),
(1772, 5, 1, 1, '2014-09-22', 'I wish I had ignored all the good reviews. Can I give it less than one star? No? Well then..one star it is. I suppose it deserves one star because it is, in fact, stainless steel and also (intended to be) a coffeemaker. It did make us a pot of coffee, it was hot and coffee-like. That was it...the second time we used it...it did not make any coffee. It\'s inexplicably busted. RIP coffee\"maker.\"'),
(1773, 12, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'durable Years later and it still works perfectly'),
(1774, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-13', 'Awesome!!! Great little coffee maker!!! Perfect for a single person use. Makes a full pot in less than 5 min!! Perfect for rushing in the morning.'),
(1775, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-17', 'Five Stars Great Product, quick delivery.'),
(1776, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', 'Glad I picked this toaster, it does everything I need. This toaster gets FIVE stars.  I like the way you can pick the DEFROST option when toasting something taken from the freezer, it defrosts AND toasts.  Not many toasters have this option, Ditto for the REHEAT option, very useful.  Bagels and other odd bakery items fit in well too. There is a feature whereby you can raised the toast when it is finished so that you can remove it without burning your fingers.  You do have to turn the darkness knob round to nearly the top to get a nice uniform  brown color.'),
(1777, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'Five Stars For the price, it can\'t be beat!  I use it everyday!'),
(1778, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-10', 'Great product and great tasting coffee Love this coffee maker.'),
(1779, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-25', 'Five Stars love this. Got a good deal'),
(1780, 8, 1, 4, '2016-03-25', 'So far so good! I am still trying to coordinate the amount ... So far so good!  I am still trying to coordinate the amount of water between the pot and the water reservoir on the coffee maker.  The grounds remain pretty wet hours after the pot has been used. I have to remember to remove the drippy filter after using.  Coffee doesn\'t come out as hot as I would like it (154 degrees), but I am used to microwaving it anyway.  This is my second Black & Decker 5 cup coffeemaker.  The first one last 4 years and then the pot warmer just stopped heating.'),
(1781, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-26', 'I can wake up to the smell of coffee, ... I can wake up to the smell of coffee, one warm cup at a time, on demand. Without the guilt of coffee pods!.'),
(1782, 3, 1, 3, '2016-01-25', 'Cannot get used to this oven. After a good deal of use I am not getting used to this oven.  It is easy to over cook items.  The electronic settings are awkward.'),
(1783, 12, 1, 4, '2015-12-23', 'Four Stars Keep up the good work.'),
(1784, 4, 1, 3, '2016-09-01', 'Caveat Emptor - Remember Mike Brady? - them who dont look, sometimes gets took. Be careful, especially if you have kids using this unit!  The TOB-40 is a smart looking economical unit. I\'ve had mine for several years now (I purchased it at Bed Bath & Beyond). Two months ago, I was even considering buying the same model for a second home, this time through Amazon (didn\'t even think of looking at the reviews, since I\'d already had mine a few years.)  However, about a month ago I noticed a slight sagging in one of the heating elements of the one unit I own.  When cool, the sag was barely noticeable. Tonight, while making some toast, I noticed the heating element actually sagging so low the crumb tray was actually turning black and the heating element seemed to be sparking.  Needless to say, I disconnected the unit.  (I feel I dodged a bullet, by having the sparking happen while I used it - my kids wouldn\'t have given it a second thought.).  I went on-line to see what could be causing this.  I cannot believe how often heating element problems seem to be coming up with this unit.  As well, some people have even complained the doors have shattered.  With such frequent complaints, I don\'t understand why the model hasn\'t been recalled.  Shouldn\'t Amazon look into this?.'),
(1785, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Makes a great cup of coffee. Yes, this Hamilton Beach has a lot of convenient features. The question is, however, does it make a great cup of coffee. The answer is a unqualified, \"yes.\"  My wife and I have had many different coffee makers during past 25 years, some less expensive than this one, some much more expensive. This particular model makes an absolutely great cup of coffee, perhaps the best tasting coffee we have had from a home coffee maker.  Great product, great price.'),
(1786, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-31', 'One Star Not upto the mark'),
(1787, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-21', 'Exceptional appliance I have to start out by saying I just love this machine.I have been in the Keurig family for years and it keeps getting better.This is actually the least inexpensive model I have owned but it is the best yet.There is an option on this brewer to make the coffee flavor stronger but even without using it,my coffee has tasted better than it ever did.It is great for my flavored coffee.I can actually taste the full flavor now.My coffee is hotter than it has ever been.The touch screen on this machine is easy and fun to use.I like the smaller profile.I am able to fit it in a little corner out of the way.I am really impressed and would recommend it to all coffee drinkers.I received this product free for testing.This is my honest review and have given my own opinion'),
(1788, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-15', 'No longer returnable - toaster quits after only four months of slight usage! After only four  months of very light usage - we only toast a couple of muffins in the morning - the toaster no longer heats up. Amazon won\'t take it back, because their policy says you can\'t return an item after a month; HOWEVER, I think a toaster should lost longer than four months. Especially for a customer who buys several items a month!! If you agree with me, please write to Amazon to support my claim - they should let me return the defective item!!'),
(1789, 5, 1, 3, '2015-04-07', 'Three Stars Great product except for how noisy it is.'),
(1790, 3, 1, 2, '2016-04-11', 'VE A PROBLEM,ME IM GOING TO PASS UP,TAKE TRULY,ID LIKE TO  MEET THE OTHERas s we must be reviewing 2 different ovens,i purchased mine,that\'s for sure! fact is,ive been using it for 2 months,am using right this moment! PROS/ IT WORKS VERY WELL AT KEEPING CONSTANT TEMP,VERY ACCURATE. CONS/ TAKE A DEEP BREATH U NEED ZOOM EYES  TO SEE THE BUTTONS,U NEED TO PRES A NUMBER OF BUTTONS PER FUNCTION (WHICH U CANT SEE,AS THEY ARE SO SMALL/ TRY ADDING TIME OR RASING OR LOWERING TEMP/TIME./ DONT BURN UR NOSE/HAIR,AS U WILL NEED TO GET WITHIN 6 INCHS TO SEE THEM. THE BUTTONS ARE PRETTY CLOSE TOGETHER AND THE SAME SHAPES,WHICH MAKES IT HARD TO S........u get the idea! NOW, IF YOU TAKE TIME TO MEMORIZE THE BUTTONS U WONT HA VE ANY PROBLEMS,ME,FRIDAY I SHOOT THE HELL OUT OF IT AT THE TOWN DUMP,AND BUY ANOTHER,WHICJ WILL NOT B A B&D. BYE'),
(1791, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-06', 'Don\'t do what I did, great product I purchased three of these over time, which is how well I\'ve liked them. I went to make (Mexican) hot chocolate. So I placed the hard bar of chocolate in the blender to pulverize it first. This was not much of an issue as I usually add the milk and that helps. The problem was I used hot milk to get it to dissolve faster. Well it worked, except the near-boiling heat from the milk ruined the seals of the cup/blender and it forever leaked. I wish they would just sell the cups because I would certainly buy extra if those to make shakes every day. Other than that, I purchased the others and the chopping motor aspect works very well without breaking. Just don\'t do what I did or you\'ll ruin the cup.'),
(1792, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-09', 'Clean up is easy and smoothies are refreshing Use it almost daily at work. Clean up is easy and smoothies are refreshing.'),
(1793, 10, 1, 2, '2015-11-21', 'Can\'t use it for hot drinks I can\'t return it bc I waited past the 30 day window. My fault, busy life. Blender top is easy crack plastic :( treat it with kid gloves. I found it at Walmart for $8.97.'),
(1794, 10, 1, 3, '2015-04-06', 'Three Stars Too flimsy!'),
(1795, 1, 1, 2, '2016-02-02', 'Miss my old Keurig! Very disappointed in the new Keurig 2.0.  I have owned a Keurig for about 5 years.  The first one I bought lasted less than a year and Keurig did replace it.  The replacement just stopped working recently and I bought this model.  It is bigger, which I don\'t like.  The sensor in the water reservoir seems off as it asks for water when it is only half empty.  I bought this because I had bought about 120 K-cups just before the previous unit died and the 2.0 doesn\'t accept most of them.  While Keurig claims it does this so you get the best coffee experience, shouldn\'t I be able to choose any coffee I like whether they sanction it or not?  It is also noisier and slower than the previous Keurig.  Sorry, Keurig, but you lost a customer.  I will most likely return it and buy a different brand.'),
(1796, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-08', 'so far so good it is working fine for what I purchased it ... so far so good it is working fine for what I purchased it for. I\'m please that I got it.'),
(1797, 2, 1, 4, '2015-09-23', 'A little retro fun This is a functional bottom line toaster oven. The timer tick tick ticks , and goes ding! when it\'s done, in a charming retro way. The crumb tray is easy to clean. It is not fancy or expensive but does its job.'),
(1798, 7, 3, 2, '2016-05-18', 'I am not impressed. If you like a warm drink, this would be for you. I like mine hot and have to put it in the microwave to heat after brewing.'),
(1799, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'Five Stars GOOD QUALITY!'),
(1800, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Super Toaster/Roaster, I\'m a boaster It\'s super. It toasts; it roasts; it boasts a whole host of things it can do. And it does them well. Buy it, stop reading this.'),
(1801, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'She did love.. Despite the adage, \"Never buy her something she has to plug in\", She did love...actually she asked for it so I was cool. works and looks great.'),
(1802, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Keurig 2.0 K200 is AMAZING! I am so in LOVE! This Keurig 2.0 K200 is AMAZING! I am so in love with this Keurig. The digital screen makes it so easy to use because it tells you what you need to do or it tells you what it is doing so your not just standing there and wondering what to do next. You can also choose what size you want between a 4, 6, 8, & 10 ounce. You can also get a Carafe which is basically a coffee pot that you can make more for either yourself or guests. The coffee flavor is way better than if you made a pot of coffee. Since we went from a regular coffee pot to a Keurig we won\'t be going back. The Keurig is staying forever! I honestly can\'t wait to get up in the morning to just get some coffee. I also love to make tea out of the Keurig and the flavor of the tea is way better also. I am very thankful that I received this Keurig free for testing. This has been the best thing ever. I am sold on the Keurig 2.0 K200.'),
(1803, 3, 1, 4, '2014-12-19', 'Four Stars Second one good product'),
(1804, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Makes a Good Cup Of Coffee This is my second Keurig. I wanted a smaller unit for the Motorhome and also wanted the ability to make several cups at a time. I have been very pleased with this Keurig 2 K200. It makes a good cup of coffee. I like being able to make a stronger cup if I want. I like being able to change the size of the cup I make(my other one also has this option). I have not purchased the carafe so I cannot comment on making several cups at one time. Plan on buying it soon. The only negative is the noise it makes while brewing. It is loud and sounds like it is working hard. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1805, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-03', 'Great toaster oven Pleased with the new toaster oven.  Easier to clean than most.  Removable tray in the bottom & grid is also removable for cleaning.'),
(1806, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-24', 'Perfect So far so good! My lid fits perfectly fine unlike other reviews. Perfect for my morning shakes.'),
(1807, 11, 1, 4, '2015-01-16', 'i\'d buy it again a great little toaster oven - which toasts three slices with ease but have to scrunch together if you want fourth on the rack (must admit that bread is rather large slice). its steady heat works well with reheating foods and cooking fish fillets was a breeze. must remember to check often so that foodstuffs don\'t burn but i imagine this is so with most small ovens. my one problem is cleaning the oven - unlike other ovens i\'ve used this doesn\'t have a removable crumb tray and access to clean with a sponge can be dicey if elements are still hot - it must be left to cool completely before trying to clean it. can recommend this to anyone wanting a smaller appliance.'),
(1808, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-18', 'so it\'s a good Toaster Oven for the price OK, so it\'s a good Toaster Oven for the price.  Is very handy to broil up a couple of pieces of fish or chicken.  I did have a major issue though.  Suddenly one evening I couldn\'t get the door to open. It was jammed stuck. I was concerned if I pulled too hard I\'d break the glass front. I yanked and tugged and pulled and pulled. I ended up calling Cuisinart, they sent me a new one, but I did realize in the time I was on the phone (about an hour) that there was a piece of the metal inside the slot blocking the hinge so I took a knife and bent it. now the door works fine again but that was annoying. There are these tiny little black buffers so the door doesn\'t slam against the metal frame that came off too.  But, all in all...it works great and looks good too. I\'m happy enough.'),
(1809, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-26', 'Best Coffeemaker Ever This is the second one we have had - first one burned out because of my own stupid fault (forgot to put the carafe in the coffeemaker which flooded the counter, floor and burner, pfhhhhsssst). I love it because it swivels around to fill so there\'s not a lot of dragging out from under the counter....and it makes fabulous coffee. We make very strong coffee so set it on BOLD. Wakes us up in the morning for sure!'),
(1810, 8, 1, 5, '2014-10-01', 'Excellent Value Very good product. I had this same brand before. It meets my needs very well. It makes a good  pot of coffee quickly.'),
(1811, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-03', 'Five Stars Toasts evenly and easy to use.'),
(1812, 5, 1, 3, '2014-03-12', 'It makes coffee It makes a cup of coffee, like its supposed to. I am rating it 3 stars because the coffee pot needs to be redesigned. Almost every day, as I am pouring coffee into my cup or thermos, the coffee tends to spill out from the sides. I think this happens because of the plastic bar that sits right at the spout, the coffee goes over the bar, and instead of coming out the spout, it comes out from the sides.'),
(1813, 1, 1, 4, '2015-11-07', 'and love that I finally have one with the water tank ... This is my second Keurig machine I\'ve owned. I previosuly owned the mini, and love that I finally have one with the water tank resevoir. I had to do a couple of vinegar washes to get rid of the burnt plastic smell, but now it works perfectly fine for my daily cup of coffee.'),
(1814, 1, 1, 1, '2016-01-13', 'Not Worth The Effort Received this as a Christmas gift. Can\'t get it to use the pods that says it will work with ALL Keurigs I bought at the grocery store and they cost way too much. Now I\'m stuck with $25.00 worth of tiny cups of coffee.  To use them, I\'ll have to open all those tiny cups. Not happening. Great hot water machine if you want hot chocolate.  Unfortunately I already had one on my old coffeemaker.  Guess it will work if you make instant coffee too. This gadget is not my cup of tea.'),
(1815, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-26', 'Good buy for the $$$$$ great coffee maker....makes good coffee every time...easy to use.'),
(1816, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-08', 'FAR superior. Of course the wax is much harder to ... The styling wax is not the same thing as the styling gel, my husband informed me. The wax is, according to him, FAR superior. Of course the wax is much harder to find in our area so I was glad to find it here. Happy husband, happy...well. I bought shoes so I am happy too.'),
(1817, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-21', 'Five Stars Great Coffee pot, easy to setup and makes a great cup of coffee.'),
(1818, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'Great toaster. Very happy with this purchase Great toaster.  Very happy with this purchase!'),
(1819, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-12', 'Great little blender Great little blender. It chews through ice and leafy greens without a problem. It makes a perfect green smoothie.'),
(1820, 7, 3, 5, '2015-03-01', 'This is a awesome coffeemaker for the price. I switched back to Hamilton Beach after several expensive makers broke.'),
(1821, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-15', 'Five Stars Does what a toaster should... Toast....'),
(1822, 6, 1, 4, '2014-06-05', 'looks nice -- works well this toaster is nice.  I like that the \"body\" of it does not get hot when using the appliance - great!'),
(1823, 12, 1, 5, '2015-11-17', 'Five Stars I love it! It\'s small, doesn\'t take up too much space and works great!'),
(1824, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-29', 'Good toaster oven but needs a different broiler pan I bought this in November of 2014 and have been pleased with it for the most part. The toaster oven works well. My only complaint is that previous toaster ovens I bought had a full broiler pan. This one only has a pan which slides out from under the grill. The pan itself does not have a non stick surface so anything that burns onto the pan is pretty much impossible to get off unless you use a knife. That, of course, scratches the surface. The only way around this would be to line the pan with aluminum foil. I do not think using this pan for broiling would be good at all. The toaster oven is best for baking and toasting.'),
(1825, 4, 1, 4, '2015-09-30', 'Four Stars Makes a bit of whitrling noise on occasion.'),
(1826, 9, 1, 2, '2015-11-16', 'Leaky lever. We have gone through 3 replacements, and every one starts leaking profusely before a year or so. The tank is difficult to clean as well, and metal head pad makes the coffee taste burnt and metallic.  We finally skipped the gimmick and went with a standard 10 Cup coffee pot.'),
(1827, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-20', 'Five Stars Works great in our breakroom at work.  Easy to clean.'),
(1828, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-13', 'Love this little toaster oven This is my second one in the last 11 years. My first one was a workhorse and was able to provide a family of 5 with many mornings of perfect toast and bagels and yummy after school warm snacks. On hot summer days it\'s nice to use for heating up small amounts so as to not heat the house by using the main oven.'),
(1829, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-11', 'Five Stars It\'s really convenient and handy'),
(1830, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-07', 'no more burned toast-I can see when I want to ... no more burned toast-I can see when I want to take it out.  Use different types of bread so they take different times to get done.  Versitle'),
(1831, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-03', 'Great Blender, especially for the price! I was hesitant to order this as I\'m not a fan of Hamilton Beach, but this little powerhouse is the greatest. I use it everyday, some days even a couple of times a day. It\'s really powerful and perfect for my shakes. It blends the ice cubes in about 30-40 seconds. The price can\'t be beat. I love this little machine.'),
(1832, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-23', 'Had to send ours back Had to send ours back, no ding when toast was ready, I read the instructions twice and confirmed that it was a defective device. The dials were a little hard to read, overall it was decently made but poor quality control.'),
(1833, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-19', 'This has got to be my favorite buy! I looked up a bunch of coffee ... This has got to be my favorite buy! I looked up a bunch of coffee pots and decided to go with this one. I highly recommend it!'),
(1834, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-19', 'Basic toaster oven that will toast bread and heat up ... Basic toaster oven that will toast bread and heat up left over pizza. Nothing much to say about it.'),
(1835, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-19', 'My God this is the best toaster I have EVER OWNED My God this is the best toaster I have EVER OWNED! I am very, pleased with it. It is fantastic. I have never had a toaster that cooks PERFECTLY EVEN EVERY TIME....yes even BAGEL...PERFECT! I would recommend this toaster for anyone who is looking for a toaster that actually does what it is supposed to do. Thanks again.'),
(1836, 5, 1, 4, '2016-03-26', 'Nearly perfect, great price Love this, makes great coffee, fast enough, however, when opening the compartment where you put the coffee and filter, the digital face plate above it keeps popping off. Not a big deal right now, but I\'m sure in time the clips will wear out. I\'d still recommend this.'),
(1837, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Works like a big blender Handy, convenient, light weight and powerful. Works like a big blender.'),
(1838, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-09', 'Will crush ice, under the right circumstances. I got this blender to make smoothies and it works wonderfully. This blender will crush ice IN MIXED DRINKS. I haven\'t tried to crush ice on its own, because well, I can tell it just wouldn\'t work. But the other day I made a pina colada and strawberry daiquiri and they came out PERFECT! I would say, with the blender being 3/4th full I put in maybe 1/4 of ice, if not less. Basically I added like two pieces of ice, blended, added two more, blended, until it was just right. With enough liquid, it will blend ice, but don\'t blend ice on it\'s own or without liquid.'),
(1839, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Great coffee all the time We\'ve had 3 different Keurig coffee makers between our family members this one is the best so far . Easy to make the larger pots you can make a stronger pot  with the checking off the box on the touch screen.'),
(1840, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'This toaster oven is perfect for my on-campus apartment This toaster oven is perfect for my on-campus apartment! It gets the job done, no more, no less. Love this gadget.'),
(1841, 9, 1, 2, '2015-02-16', 'Two Stars I used it for 3 weeks only. It started to leak everywhere. I will try a different product'),
(1842, 4, 1, 1, '2015-01-06', 'SO DISAPPOINTING -- PLEASE READ! I\'ve always been pleased with Cuisinart products.  After my experience with Cuisinart TOB-40 Custom Classic Toaster Oven Broiler, however, I\'ve totally changed my mind about anything Cuisinart! I have had excellent results from my toaster oven at home and wanted to replicate that experience at our vacation home.  I did a thorough investigation of all toaster ovens small enough to store in our vacation home kitchen cabinet.  Aside from not hot having a timer, this Cuisinart toaster oven with its 1800 watts seemed to meet our criteria. There are two slots in which to insert the oven rack.  If the rack is inserted in the higher of the two slots, it automatically comes out -- as advertised -- when the door is opened.  If does not, however, automatically come out when inserted in the lower slot. There are three recommended Rack Positions.  Position A, for baking pizzas, cake, chicken or muffins, is when the rack is inserted down in the lower slot.  Position B, for broiling or baking nachos or potatoes, is when the rack is inserted up in the lower slot.  Position C, for toast, bagels and open-faced sandwiches, is when the rack is inserted down in the upper slot. I\'ve only used this toaster oven a handful of times because I\'m afraid it will cause a fire!  I was excited when it first arrived and immediately began to prepare my husband\'s favorite salmon dish that very evening.  After reading all the directions, I proceeded to bake the salmon filet @ 450 for 5 minutes.  Smoke billowed forth from the top vents and oven door within minutes, causing me to immediately turn it off and pull out the plug.  I then had to turn on my regular oven, wait till it preheated to the correct temperature and finish cooking the salmon.  Since I wanted to give it a fair trial, I turned on the nearby vent from my microwave/stove unit prior to trying it again at a slightly lower temperature. Sadly, the result was the same. Not wanting to give up, I tried a number of cakes, cornbread, muffins and biscuits.  I\'ve come to the conclusion that Position A is too close to the bottom heating element, thus heating the bottom of baked good irregularly.  Position C is too close to the top heating element with equally disappointing results. I found six reports on www.saferproducts.gov concerning the defective heating elements.  It is dangerous and should be recalled. The temperature always seems higher than what is set on the temperature dial as proven by the irregular/darkened outside of most everything I\'ve made The outside of the toaster oven gets excessively hot whenever it is turned on. The dials are difficult to read. Lastly, I find it telling that the Cuisinart TOB-40 Custom Classic Toaster Oven Broiler lists for $145 but reduced to $69.01 when I bought it from Amazon last March, 2014 and now even lower.'),
(1843, 3, 1, 4, '2015-08-05', 'Big, make sure you have room This was bought to replace a regular toaster oven and I did not think about the dimensions. This is much larger than the 6 piece (really 4) toaster oven it replaced. Nice toaster, easily fits 6 pieces of toast, my one complaint would be the short cord.'),
(1844, 7, 3, 3, '2015-12-13', 'Will give you a cup of coffee with any K-cup brand. Sometimes needs a second press of the button to receive all the water you place in the machine.'),
(1845, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'marvelous This is a marvelous machine. Excellent control over toasting. Love the lift option so I can get at an English muffin or bagel. And the cancel button is also great. Can\'t think of anything else I need or want.'),
(1846, 1, 1, 2, '2016-08-30', 'Too finicky I\'ve owned a Keurig original for 3 years without a single issue. In the first couple weeks of using this 2.0, it\'s just too finicky. It frequently gives an error that it can\'t read the proprietary Keurig labeling on K-cups, or that I need to use the needle cleaning tool (which is strange given that it\'s brand new), and now my wife received a water pressure error. Keurig did not think this model through or test it well, so stick with the classic. The only reason it got 2 stars is because the brewing strength is a nice feature.'),
(1847, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Excellent! For the price this is perfect. In stores now is so limited and they usually have only high priced coffee makers on the shelf. Very pleased with this one.'),
(1848, 9, 1, 4, '2015-09-08', 'Four Stars It does everything it is supposed to.'),
(1849, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-10', 'Nice convenient blender Nice convenient blender. Just be attentive of what you put into it, i remind you that it\'s just a little tiny blender. Sometimes I have to shake it while blending but it does the job. Both of my sisters now have one because of me'),
(1850, 6, 1, 4, '2016-05-22', 'Looks great, almost feels cheap from it being the cool ... Looks great, almost feels cheap from it being the cool touch side style. Adjust carefully! If 1 round doesn\'t toast good enough IT WIll BURN on the second round. 3 is as high as I turn mine up. Yes there\'s a burning chemical-like smell on first use, that\'s normal, it goes away. All in all great toaster.'),
(1851, 3, 1, 4, '2015-11-12', 'Great toaster, only had it a few weeks but ... Great toaster, only had it a few weeks but love it so far.  Toasts, bakes pretty evenly.  Looks very nice with the rest of my stainless steel appliances.  Wish it had a lever or something to pull the tray out when the door opens - that\'s the reason for the 4 stars.'),
(1852, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-04', 'Great coffee maker - great price - GREAT COFFEE. I bought this coffee maker about a month ago and I LOVE it.  I had a Hamilton Beach coffee maker for many years and it finally gave out.  In desperation I brought out our Keurig while searching for a new coffee maker with the same features as our old Hamilton Beach.  I\'m so glad I found it on Amazon.  The water reservoir is removable for easy filling and the swing out basket is convenient and easy to clean.  No clumsy parts to get dirty and messy from brewing - just nice flat surfaces for easy wipes.  It\'s a nice compact size and fits under the cabinet with ease.  The coffee tastes great and beats the Keuring hands down.  You won\'t be disappointed with this coffee maker - I\'m not.'),
(1853, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-19', 'but great workhorse broiler and toaster It\'s larger than i thought, but great workhorse broiler and toaster.'),
(1854, 8, 1, 5, '2014-10-08', 'Great 5 cup Coffeemaker from Black & Decker! Package arrived on time in excellent condition.  It works great, nice to have a great working coffee pot to have my morning coffee.  Thank you Amazon.  A++++'),
(1855, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-10', 'This is a great design. It holds the hot coffee inside This is a great design. It holds the hot coffee inside. You can clean the inside and the water container. Easy cleanup for safe drinkable coffee was a key feature I insisted on when choosing my new coffee machine. This delivers. My old machine made it hard to clean out the water reservoir. Everything was inside, and there was no auto-clean feature to clean the hoses and small parts around the water pump. The old Mr. C***ee brand looked clean, but deep inside it wasn\'t. That\'s no longer an issue for me. Now my coffee tastes fresher and I have piece of mind because I know it\'s clean. The last comment I have is that I live on the coast where there are gnats in the summer. Having everything inside is some protection against bugs getting into your coffee (at least until you have it in your cup). Drink up!'),
(1856, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-10', 'Five Stars Perfect size for smoothies, and it is easy to clean.'),
(1857, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-23', 'Five Stars reliable with good features'),
(1858, 12, 1, 4, '2014-01-09', 'It is so useful, I wish it was a bit bigger. I like the fact that it is two things in one, saves on time and is very convenient. Though if it had been a little bigger, it would have been better. Apart from that, there are no disadvantages.'),
(1859, 12, 1, 5, '2014-10-01', 'this was a replacement toaster just like the one I had prior to this one like ... this was a replacement toaster just like the one I had prior to this one  like the old one thst is why I got the new one'),
(1860, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-24', 'Purchased as a gift and my sister is obsessed with it! Purchased this for my sister for Christmas.  She is obsessed with it.  The style and stainless matches her kitchen perfectly.  She constantly sends me pictures of things she cooks in the oven.  It is big enough to make pizzas as described.  Definitely a recommended!'),
(1861, 3, 1, 1, '2016-07-07', 'Does not toast. started smoking on first time use. Item being returned. Does not toast. started smoking on first time use. Item being returned.'),
(1862, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-31', 'Amazing! Great product! Blends frozen fruit excellent! Perfect for the dorm life.'),
(1863, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Hamilton Beach is a winner Hamilton Beach really has their act together for small kitchen appliances.  I\'ve been extremely happy with this coffeemaker as well as their electric tea kettle and digital toaster.  They\'re all simple devices, but Hamilton Beach really sweats the details and gets everything right.'),
(1864, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-02', 'One Star Item all dented . Let\'s see how long it\'s going to work- unsatisfactory'),
(1865, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'Five Stars best toaster oven I ever owned.'),
(1866, 4, 1, 5, '2016-11-05', 'Super cooker! I am use to my old toaster ... Super cooker! I am use to my old toaster oven, so this fast cooket will take some time to get use to.'),
(1867, 3, 1, 4, '2016-07-23', 'good customer service the stainless steel is very thin. My oven arrived with a small dent at the top. There is no light inside when the cooking element is active so you cannot see the food. I had an Oster prior to this that I like better. However since I have no major complaints I kept the oven. After my original review, I was contacted by the company representative who offered to replace the unit. I did not feel the small dent warranted replacement but was very impressed with the way the company responded. It is unusual to get that kind of rapid response from most companies. For that reason I chose to give them four stars.'),
(1868, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-08', 'oven toaster Great oven toaster, it just helps a lot in heating and reheating food in the kitchen'),
(1869, 2, 1, 2, '2015-11-27', 'You get what you pay for Bought this basic toaster oven at the end of June and it\'s already dead. Doesn\'t toast the bread, just dries it out.'),
(1870, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-25', 'Great coffee machine, wish we\'d gotten one sooner. Fantastic coffee machine, both my wife and I love it. Works perfectly and makes great coffee. Easy to clean and easy to use everyday.'),
(1871, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-13', 'No Longer a Good Toaster I had the old model of this toaster for many years.  It always worked well, which is why I decided to buy another one.  The new model does not work good at all.  The dial feels like it is going to fall off it is so loose, so I was skeptical that it would do anything when I tried to toast something.  Sure enough I was right-no matter what setting I put it on nothing happened.  The bread pops back up in a few seconds and it is not toasted, even when it is set between 4-5.  I returned this toaster.'),
(1872, 2, 1, 2, '2016-04-30', 'Not worth the money Poorly designed. Its not user friendly. I  know its  just a toaster oven, how complicated could it be, right??  But my mom and husband agree with me. The on/off button is not clear, the timer stays on  even though the bread is burning.  I  figured B& D  is a good, reputable brand but they totally missed it. The cost of returning it its half the price of this item, so Im stucked with this piece, hopefully for not too long'),
(1873, 9, 1, 3, '2016-12-24', 'This is our 2nd Coffee-on-Demand pot and with love the pot This is our 2nd Coffee-on-Demand pot and with love the pot.  Unfortunately, they shortened the electrical cord on the newer version and we have to have an extension cord connected to it to move it out from under our cabinets.  Poor design as far as I\'m concerned.'),
(1874, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-31', 'Five Stars A great product. Never an issue and used many times. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1875, 3, 1, 1, '2016-06-29', 'Have now received two defective toasters in one week! ... Have now received two defective toasters in one week! Very frustrating. Both missing components of the feet and the second scratched in multiple places with warped metal.'),
(1876, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-12', 'and its easy to burn something if you aren\'t very careful The toast function is very sensitive, and its easy to burn something if you aren\'t very careful. however, it works fine in general and is definitely a good value for the price.'),
(1877, 9, 1, 2, '2016-01-03', 'Cord is short, no go. I bought this on a flash sale. Somehow I missed that this was a 12-cup coffee maker, which is OK. However, when we set it up the cord is only 2 inches long. The manufacturer says in the instructions that it\'s short because it could get tangled. They said you could use an extension cord, which seems even more dangerous! And no, it did not pull out/retract. Sent it right back.'),
(1878, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-10', 'Thank you It\'s ergonomic layout made me extremely pleased with my purchase. It\'s very easy to clean as well,.'),
(1879, 12, 1, 5, '2015-09-13', 'I like having a toaster/oven I bought this one to replace a previous one that finally went out. I like having a toaster/oven.'),
(1880, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-02', 'a recommended buy A very nice unit good quality'),
(1881, 5, 1, 3, '2017-01-05', 'I ordered this in april 2016. The face plate ... I ordered this in april 2016 . The face plate broke off not even 6 months later. The buttons also shift because of the broken face plate. It does still brew for now.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1882, 9, 1, 4, '2015-03-04', 'We love this new coffee maker We love this new coffee maker.  This is our second one of this model and we love the new changes on this one.....the light to show how full your cup is.. it\'s also much easier to fill the tank .  The gauge to show how full the tank is is not very good.......it could be better but altogether it\'s a great coffee maker.  Will buy another when we wear this one out.  Had to take off one star because of the gauge..'),
(1883, 2, 1, 3, '2015-04-09', 'It does all it is supposed to do but the handle gets hot. It does all it is supposed to do but the handle gets hot. Product works but probably just a bad design.'),
(1884, 11, 1, 1, '2016-03-12', 'One Star It broke after a a couple of months'),
(1885, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-14', 'Five Stars I like mine. Bought for our motor home. Because it is smaller then most toaster ovens'),
(1886, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-03', 'Five Stars It\'s amazing, I simply love it!'),
(1887, 5, 1, 4, '2016-11-26', 'Four Stars easy to use.  not the best looking coffee maker, but it works for us!.'),
(1888, 9, 1, 3, '2016-01-11', 'Cuisinart does not back up their warranty or product! The coffee maker was great until the first time we had to clean it. It is self cleaning and has a light to let you know when to do it. After the light comes on you cannot make coffee until you do the cleaning. Well after we ran the cleaning cycle, it would not make coffee. We called Cuisinart and they said they would replace it.  That was on December 18 and we still have not received the replacement like they said. They were quite rude about the fact that we bought it on Amazon, so I am not sure if that is why they haven\'t done anything. We are still trying to get it replaced, we should have gone through Amazon, but figured it came under the manufacturers warranty, which it should have. It is a lot of money for a machine the company will not back up. I bought it because it is suppose to be made in America, but I will not support Cuisinart any more. We had 2 weeks of good coffee, back to a Mr. Coffee.'),
(1889, 5, 1, 4, '2014-07-26', 'Four Stars satisfied with product'),
(1890, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-05', 'Five Stars Works great! I hope this one last as my old one, many years.'),
(1891, 12, 1, 5, '2014-06-19', 'Room saver for RV Works just as advertised and is doing a great job in my RV. Others have said they are going to get one too.'),
(1892, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-26', 'Best oven toaster ever made! Cuisinart does make the best oven toaster in the world. I think it toasts bread easily and it quickly reheats my other favorite breakfast food like bagels and sandwiches too.'),
(1893, 2, 1, 1, '2016-01-06', 'really disappointed Didn\'t came with internal parts , really disappointed'),
(1894, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-01', 'My third K machine died, but I still had a large box of cups Bought this one Makes a better cup of coffee and its hot hot love it Also make a cup of regular (grounds) brewed coffee and great tea with bags or loose leaf.'),
(1895, 7, 3, 1, '2014-07-16', 'Bought this product to take a on a family vacation. The first time we pulled it out, it took several tries to make the k-cup work properly (Assembly is very flimsy). Once we had it working it made two separate cups of coffee and after that would not produce anymore. It made lots of notice like it was working but no fluid actually came out. Tried several times, disassembled what we could to see if something was clogged, but could not diagnose. Be careful with this one.'),
(1896, 2, 1, 2, '2016-08-06', 'Otherwise I do like it, but something is obviously defective I bought this item then started using it about 14 months ago.  In the past month or two the interior has started flaking off onto our food.  I have no idea what\'s going on but I am starting the process of replacing it.  It supposedly has a two year warranty so I\'m hoping things will go smoothly.  Otherwise I do like it, but something is obviously defective.'),
(1897, 6, 1, 3, '2015-03-27', 'Three Stars It toast unevenly.'),
(1898, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-24', 'Nice toaster Oven Does a nice job for a reasonable price'),
(1899, 5, 1, 3, '2016-07-10', 'Not as great as I thought Bought it for my mother. She loved it for a whole year! It just should have lasted more than that :( She took perfect care of it! Coffee tasted great and loved the timer feature.'),
(1900, 11, 1, 4, '2014-07-07', 'Good things come in little pacakages. To be so small, it works well. I have cooked chicken legs and steak and it really works well. Fits well on my small counter. I cannot complain. I am happy I bought it.'),
(1901, 11, 1, 1, '2014-03-27', 'Danger, do not buy I had this for a few month. The timer stopped working and goes past the off point and onto the stay on. It never turns off! I had to unplug and then tried to test it a few times. It won\'t stop at off. Terrible feature and very unsafe. If I had not been in the room and noticed or just assumed the oven would go off, a fire would have started.'),
(1902, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-12', 'perfectly simple and fast It\'s the perfect juicer for me. It\'s simple, it juices fast, and it juices plenty.'),
(1903, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-10', 'Performs Beautifully! It performs beautifully! Compact design, easy access (no top clearance required), and no drips! It looks great too! I\'m extremely pleased with this product!'),
(1904, 5, 1, 1, '2016-07-25', 'The plate that covers the buttons doesn\'t stay on, ... The plate that covers the buttons doesn\'t stay on, so every time we open the area that holds the grinds, it pops off :(.'),
(1905, 12, 1, 1, '2015-07-25', 'short oven and more failing points The opening for the oven is a little short, otherwise good. UPDATE: The toaster doesn\'t work right - you have to flip the bread over - top to bottom - to get an even toastiness. Also, there is no tray on the bottom. The height of the oven is so small I can\'t even bake a regular size baked potato. If you are not careful, the item (s) in the oven will slip behind the grate and, if you have preheated the unit, you have to let it cool to reach back there and retrieve it. The cord is very short (and so am I) so I have to stretch to reach it when it\'s plugged in. Lastly, - and this might not be true for everyone, but when I set it to any temperature above 300 it pops the breaker on that side of the boat (yes, I live on a house boat). It uses more electricity (watts) then the breaker can handle. So...I really wish I had had more of a chance to use it sooner (as I got it as a gift and it sat in the box for two weeks) . It is now no longer eligible for a return. I really wish I had ordered the newer model and spent the few extra bucks since the new one is 10\' taller and somewhat deeper and comes with a tray. Don\'t make the mistake I did - get the newer one! Someone shopping at Goodwill will get a great deal on a nearly new product...The only thing I can say about it good is that it is red as are all my other counter top appliances.'),
(1906, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-22', 'I really like that it stays cool so you can\'t get accidently ... was replacing my old toaster and this one is same brand just a newer version.  I really like that it stays cool so you can\'t get accidently burned.'),
(1907, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'A great all-around drip coffeemaker! Excellent coffee maker with reliably dripless, pour a cup feature, removable water reservoir, and easy programming. I\'ve had a variety of better quality drip coffee makers, but this one seems to have most of the features one would want in a reliable, sharp design. The only thing I would change is to include the (optional) water filter and possibly redesign the water tank to be on the side rather the back for ease of access. In any regard, a nice, full-featured coffeemaker that really works well.'),
(1908, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-10', 'Works great We have had this toaster for about a month and so far so good! We use it on setting 3 and it toasts perfectly and doesn\'t ever burn the toast.'),
(1909, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-18', 'Simple to use I love my Keurig 2.0 brewing machine. I\'m a newbie to Keurig products and was hesitant about the product. However, the product is convenient, user friendly and simple to use. I no longer have to use the old school method of brewing a whole pot of coffee for one cup of coffee. The other nice thing about the Keurig is the variety, I also enjoy the teas, apple ciders and hot chocolates I have option to brew with the machine. I absolutely recommend the Keurig 2.0! \" Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(1910, 10, 1, 1, '2016-03-29', 'Fire in the Kitchen?! The first time I received this item, I was immediately disappointed to see that the food inside was not turning as I had expected it to, no matter how long I tried. Upon further inspection, I saw that the blade wasn\'t even turning. Great. I pressed the button a little longer, hoping for a miracle, only to see the item start smoking. That was not so great. After some tears (from frustration and hunger) and a couple emails, I arranged to send the faulty product back to the manufacturer in exchange for a working one. After waiting another two weeks, the new product arrived; and this time, started blending right away. I spent two glorious months with this little guy. We went everywhere together: to class, grocery shopping, even to the doctor\'s office. However, after a mere five uses, things started going south. Slowly but surely, he stopped blending. I would find entire chunks of fruit in my smoothie; but still, I persevered. After seven or eight uses, he started screaming. I do not know how else to describe the sound that this blender made with any word from the English language other than \"screaming\".  My dog howled in despair and my roommate ran into the kitchen, asking who was being murdered. But still, I persevered. On the tenth use, while I watched my fruit stir sluggishly in the blender and heard the scream of the motor, I started to smell smoke. Soon after, I saw the smoke. There was so much smoke, you guys. I quickly lifted it out of its pod to run it under cold water. As I did so, it started falling apart in my hands. I watched pieces fall on the floor as I cried; the blender crumbling like my heart. So, I bid adieu to this product for good, along with the twenty-odd dollars I lost to it.'),
(1911, 6, 1, 2, '2015-08-22', 'Does not have a bagel mode There\'s a lot to like about this toaster, but if you toast bagels TURN BACK NOW. It toasts evenly and fits some of the biggest breads. Seems sturdy. Unfortunately, no one at Cuisinart has ever toasted a bagel. They falsely claim that this toaster has a bagel function. It does not. Their \"bagel\" function toasts each side for twice the duration. Huh?? A real bagel function toasts only one side of the bagel. This toaster does not have that functionality. It\'s as deceiving as if I sold you a car and said it had airbags, only to find out my definition of airbags is pillows in the headrest. Instead of a nicely toasted bagel on the cut side only, you get an extra crispy bagel that\'s toasted on both sides...'),
(1912, 6, 1, 2, '2015-08-08', 'Only toasts one side of the bread. Have to ... Only toasts one side of the bread. Have to rotate bread and toast a bit more to get both sides toasted!'),
(1913, 11, 1, 4, '2014-03-02', 'Good for the most part I bought this toaster oven mainly because of its compact size: it fits right on top of my tiny microwave, but it still is roomy enough to hold a personal pizza, three whole medium potatoes, one peeled and chopped potato, or 4 small pieces of bread for toasting. My oven takes a long time to heat, so I really like that this toaster oven heats in 5 minutes. It\'s perfect for small meals and I\'m very happy with my purchase. My only complaint is that like other people pointed out, this toaster oven tends to burn toasts, but there\'s a fix for that. I found that toasting for 2 minutes gives me a good, lightly brown toast. It took me  a while to figure out, and until I did, I ate many a blackened toast. In all, it\'s a good buy for people with small kitchens and people with small families.'),
(1914, 5, 1, 1, '2016-11-03', 'The coffee in both isn\'t just bad, it\'s impossible to drink We got 2 of these as housewarming gifts in July.  The coffee in both isn\'t just bad, it\'s impossible to drink.  It tastes like plastic. Other reviews online suggest that these coffeemakers were made from a bad batch of plastic and the plastic leaches into the coffee. That\'s the only answer that makes sense for how bad this coffee is.  If you make 3 or 4 pots consecutively, the 4th pot might not be as bad as the first.  But now that I\'ve read how the plastic leaches into the coffee, I won\'t even be trying to fix coffee in these again. I\'m very upset that I actually drank any of this \'coffee\' at all.'),
(1915, 7, 3, 5, '2016-04-09', 'I gave it to a coworker as a gift. She loves it and says it works great.'),
(1916, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'I love this thing I love this thing. It makes coffee, tea, cocoa, cappuccino and it\'s super fast and simple. Cleanup is super easy as well. The only down side is my dishwasher stays full of mugs. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1917, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-22', 'So far so great No complaints yet and I am very hopeful based on the thoughtful design that this one will also last longer than the experience I have had with some of the more expensive brands I have tried. Call me crazy but I remember the good ol\' days when you could get more  than 6 months or a year out of a coffee maker! As other reviewers have stated, I love the detachable reservoir and the easy access for the coffee grounds. If it keeps doing what it is doing I will be ecstatic with this purchase.'),
(1918, 8, 1, 4, '2016-03-03', 'but it makes a fine cup of coffee Cheap, simple, and does what it\'s supposed to do.  No auto-shutoff or timer, but it makes a fine cup of coffee.'),
(1919, 7, 3, 4, '2014-05-10', 'I always clean after I brew \' cause I want pure taste of each varied K-cups. I\'ve had mine for a month; my hope is for this to last for years. A particular Espresso brand spews coffee granules on the holder--but that\'s not the only brand I use.I do the alternative basket for this particular \'Espresso\'. All in all this is the most used single brewer in my apartment.'),
(1920, 2, 1, 2, '2016-07-22', 'You get what you pay for... But ... You get what you pay for... But it gets the job done. When toasting, make sure you flip and turn your food as it doesn\'t heat evenly.'),
(1921, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Perfect Blender for a Single Person I this blender. It perfect for the single individual. It\'s convenient and just the right size to make a smoothie or protein shake to take with you.'),
(1922, 5, 1, 4, '2015-10-25', 'Four Stars OK but not the best'),
(1923, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-01', 'Makes great smoothies. You have to baby it a bit cause it\'s not real powerful.  But I gave two as Christmas presents, then I had to go back and get another for someone that didn\'t get one.  Now all three people have them and really like them.  They use them all the time and it has provided them with a healthier eating habit.  It takes up minimal space on the counter, so you can leave it out.  I highly recommend getting this but remember it has to be used carefully.  If you push it too hard you will burn out the motor..'),
(1924, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-12', 'Five Stars Great price with plenty of features found in more expensive units.'),
(1925, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Really like this coffee maker Really like this coffee maker.  Makes great coffee. Super easy to clean. Love that it has its own water filter. Tastes gets a bit off after being on for couple hours. Some days I think I miss the kuerig but for ease of cleaning & adjusting strength etc.... great with this one.'),
(1926, 2, 1, 1, '2016-07-07', 'Toaster oven went up in flames Was toasting some corn tortillas and turned my back for a second. Turned around and the entire toaster oven was in flames. Set off the fire alarm, made my dogs go crazy, and permanently damaged my cabinets. All while on \"toast\" for about 3 minutes. VERY DANGEROUS unit, please be careful when purchasing. Check \"consumer reports\" online for this product and you will see review and review of the glass shattering and the food and machine catching on fire.'),
(1927, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', 'TOAST AWAY Just got this new model to replace our old Cuisinart toaster and it works like a charm. Love the 4 wide slots for thicker goodies.'),
(1928, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-10', 'Four Stars It\'s a reasonable price for me.'),
(1929, 3, 1, 1, '2015-01-22', 'Does not last My wife and I got this as a wedding gift. It worked well but does get very hot on all sides including the control panel. It seemed to run colder than the digital display but that is easily compensated for. The reason I am giving it one star is because after about a year and a half of light use the top elements have stopped working. Now it has a top temperature of about 225 making it useless. I plan to buy a new toaster oven but I will try a different brand.'),
(1930, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'This is a wonderful toaster and I love the white color For those tired of stainless steel.  This is a wonderful toaster and I love the white color.'),
(1931, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-10', 'Four Stars Works as advertised. My only complaint is the dials are a bit confusing at first.'),
(1932, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-19', 'Four Stars Good product-good price'),
(1933, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Nice fill feature I absolutely love it! It sits under my cabinet & no need to pull out to make coffee!'),
(1934, 4, 1, 2, '2015-12-21', 'Don\'t waste your money on this toaster oven Don\'t waste your money on this toaster oven, unless you plan on standing next to it and watching for yourself to see when the toast is finished.  No matter where you set the toast setting, it will either go off after 30 seconds without toasting or completely burn it.  There is really no in between.  It isn\'t just my toaster as others have complained of this AND, the first one I received did this.  I sent it back and got the one that I have now that I didn\'t get around to sending back.  Oven works great, though.'),
(1935, 9, 1, 5, '2015-06-17', 'This is a great product, I should have bought two of them This is a great product, I should have bought two of them, they have gone up 20 dollars since I purchased mine a couple months ago.'),
(1936, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-16', 'Not the best, not the worst Definitely toasts things. Though I wish I had gotten the convection oven one instead... but it\'ll do...'),
(1937, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Great for a one coffee-drinker-household! I\'ve only had my brewer for a week and I love it! My old single cup brewer required me to fill it up with water for each use. I love the reservoir and the bright screen with easy to use directions. I hope Keurig comes out with their own reusable pod for this machine. I highly recommend this machine for those who are the sole coffee drinkers in their household. Also, Thank you Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(1938, 2, 1, 2, '2016-02-23', 'Too small for us. I bought this based on several positive reviews, but it ended up being too small.  You really have to watch what you put in there so it doesn\'t get burned.  I\'m going to donate it to my office break room and go guy a bigger one someplace else where I can actually look at the oven in person instead of ordering online.'),
(1939, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-01', 'Awesome! Love this convection plus steamer!  Still need to explore some recipes, but it\'s beautiful and gets questions from visitors.'),
(1940, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-21', 'Better than my previous toaster oven Excellant..toasts without me watching...toaster oven is much more efficient than my other one.'),
(1941, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', 'Five Stars Very good for the price.'),
(1942, 5, 1, 4, '2016-12-05', 'Four Stars MY WIFE\'S LOVE THIS MACHINE.GOOD QUALITY.'),
(1943, 4, 1, 1, '2016-08-02', 'DANGEROUS-DON\'T BUY Dangerous.  Top surface temperature reaches 242 degrees.  Have talked to manufacturer several times asking them to notify owners.  Absolutely no cooperation from Cuisinart.  Have filed formal complaint with Consumer Safety Commission.  This should be taken off of Amazon.'),
(1944, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-01', 'Excellet toaster oven - versatile and efficient This is the best toaster. It\'s large enough to heat a few slices of pizza or cook a potpie or pie. The best thing (and the main reason we got it) was so that we could make baked potatoes without feeling like we were wasting electricity. It\'s large enough to be versatile with foods that you cook, but small enough to be easily moved and cleaned. We have one of these at work, so i had insider knowledge when buying. For the price, you really can\'t lose. I did my research and couldn\'t find a better deal.'),
(1945, 9, 1, 1, '2016-02-15', 'Not happy about having a product that stopped working shortly after I got it and then find out I can\'t return it! Loved this product then one morning just after a few weeks use it stopped working. No warning of anything wrong just stopped working!!!! I checked to return it and it could not be returned. Very disappointed, it was fairly expensive, I thought it would have been under warranty at least 90 days, but that was not the case. I will be more careful about buying this type of product.'),
(1946, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-20', 'It doesn\'t drip! Replaced a KitchenAid unit which cost 3X as much.  Doesn\'t have a water filter, but don\'t I need one as I feed this with a Brita filter/pitcher.  A bit slower brewing than previous KitchenAids and Cuisinarts.  Same good quality brewing.  Unlike others, it keeps it selections between uses.  FINALLY, A COFFEE MAKER WITH A NON_DRIP CARAFE!  A great deal - I\'ll forgive the slow brew to avoid the messy pouring.'),
(1947, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-31', 'super super.'),
(1948, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Best Coffee Maker I\'ve had Love this coffee maker.  I had a Mr. Coffee and it only lasted 1-2 years.  That didn\'t seem like much to me so I wanted to try a different brand name.  I picked this one because of the reviews.  I didn\'t exactly get what was meant by having a separate tank for filling but I tried it anyway.  What it has is a plastic tank (so to speak) that is the same height and width of the base unit on the back of the unit.  It comes off and you can fill it up and put it back on.  It is easy to use and comes in handy if you don\'t want to throw the last cup out but want your coffee ready to go in the morning. It took me a bit to get used to but now I love that feature. My husband works 2nd shift and sometimes likes to finish the pot when he gets home. I especially like the LED display, as well.  It is bright and easy to read.  Last, but not least, I love that the auto programming feature is so easy to use.  I\'ve had many coffee makers with that feature and for the most part it seemed more trouble than it was worth to fool with it.  This is a snap.  I would absolutely buy this again.'),
(1949, 8, 1, 3, '2014-03-16', 'OK, But Died After 18 Months We wanted a small coffee maker to replace one we used for about 8 years.  This product seemed good and it fit in the appliance garage on the counter.  It made \"OK\" coffee.  The on/off light stopped working during the first month.  The other day it stopped working while brewing, then started up again about 20 minutes later.  Upon examination, coffee was leaking through the base of the unit onto the counter.  Time to go shopping again.  I feel it should have lasted longer than 18 months. UPDATE:  Spectrum Brands contacted me and sent me a replacement--received early April 2014.  Great customer service.  I will post again if another update is needed.'),
(1950, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-25', 'Five Stars can\'t wait to use it.'),
(1951, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-14', 'It\'s toasting timer is great and I highly recommend it\'s purchase This toaster oven works perfectly. It\'s toasting timer is great and I highly recommend it\'s purchase. Plus, Amazon\'s speedy delivery was greatly appreciated after our toaster oven suddenly quit. Thank You'),
(1952, 4, 1, 2, '2016-05-27', 'Kaput ! The electrical component of this product zoned out after four months. Kaput!  Buyer should purchase a different brand. See other online comments.'),
(1953, 4, 1, 1, '2015-08-03', 'The heating element on the bottom started warping and bent ... The heating element on the bottom started warping and bent down so far that it reached the crumb tray and would light any food on the tray on fire!!!!'),
(1954, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'I love this Keurig I love this Keurig!  This is my first single cup brewer and it brews a phenomenal cup of coffee.  I will never own another type of coffee pot.  The K Cups are more expensive than what we were brewing in our coffee pot, but the taste of this coffee is well worth the difference.  I am using spring water in the K250, as our water is very hard.  I have had this Keurig for 2 weeks now and have nothing negative to say.  Amazing coffee shop quality coffee.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1955, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'A+ model yup really good model. compact yet lots if settings to choose from. if recommend over any one cup- including other Keurig one-cup brewer for sure!'),
(1956, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-09', 'Just an OK brewer I don\'t drink a ton of coffee but what I do drink is almost exclusively Dunkin K-Cups. I was pleased to see they had already upgraded their K-Cups to work on the 2.0 machines so the ones I already had would work in this machine. This machine brews up to a 10oz cup and has a strong setting that you can select. It will also dispense hot water in up to 6oz doses. You can also purchase an optional carafe and use carafe K-Cups to brew up to 4 cups of coffee. In the box they also give you a needle maintenance tool, descaling solution, a couple of water filters, and 4 sample cups. After using the machine for a couple of weeks it seems to work mostly as expected. After using the machine for a day I figured out that you have to hold your finger on the power button to actually turn the machine off. It doesn\'t seem to have an auto-off like my old brewer. I don\'t like this very much. It is kind of hard to believe that there is no auto-off function anymore. I don\'t like the tank on the back very much. It is an awkward shape to hold while filling and carrying around with water in it.  Also it is awkward when you are trying to place it on the back of the machine while it is sitting on a counter top with cabinets over it. It is very easy to accidentally spill while doing these activities. Overall the machine works but I wouldn\'t say it is outstanding.'),
(1957, 3, 1, 5, '2014-08-21', 'Convenient for many purposes I haven\'t owned a toaster oven before, and I bought this one based on features, price, and good reviews. It\'s quite a bit larger than the four-slice toaster that it replaced, so I had to rearrange the kitchen counter a bit. The toaster oven is about 19\" wide, but I leave about 3\" clearance on each side, so it takes up about 25\" of running counter space. On my counter, it plugs in directly behind the unit, so it winds up being about 15\" deep, to leave about 4\" clearance from the wall, so the toaster oven metalwork doesn\'t press against the plug in the electric outlet. I have about 8\" clearance above the unit to the overhead wooden cabinets, which seems very comfortable. I measure the electric cord to be about 24\" long; it comes out of the back of the right side of the unit, looking from the front. As others have observed, the entire outer surface of the unit gets hot with use. The only safe things to touch during use are the door handle and the control push buttons. If you don\'t touch anything else with your bare fingers, you will be fine. The only things I store on top of the unit are the metal pan/tray/rack that go in the unit, I wouldn\'t store anything else on top due to the heat. I think the controls are a little complicated, but by going slowly and thinking about what I\'m doing, I can usually manage to press the correct buttons in the correct order. Basically what you do is press a mode button (like Bake), then the up/down buttons to change the temperature setting (if desired) which is flashing on the display, then the Timer button (time now flashes on the display) followed by up/down to change the time duration (if desired), followed by the Start/Stop button. Once a Bake operation starts, you can press the Convection button to start the internal fan. It\'s no big deal if I make a mistake or forget what I was doing, because it\'s easy enough to wait a few seconds for the control panel to time out, then re-enter the correct sequence from the beginning. It\'s a little annoying trying to change the temp/time numbers because they flash on and off slowly, so you only see the value half of the time. I have noticed that some frozen foods say not to cook them in a toaster oven, which confused me. After researching the issue, I discovered that the reason is that a toaster oven is small and not very powerful, compared to a full-size oven. Therefore when you cook a significant amount of frozen food in a toaster oven, the food may cook unevenly and perhaps incompletely. For pre-cooked frozen food that you merely have to heat up, that\'s not such a problem. But other frozen food starts out raw and must be cooked thoroughly, and incomplete cooking can cause food-borne illness. One way to minimize the problem is to use a cooking tray without a rim, such as a small baking sheet or even just the wire rack, and then turn on the convection fan to distribute the heat better. Trays that have a lip or rim, especially a substantial one, can interfere with air circulation and heat distribution, so items near the rim can be undercooked. Another way to avoid the problem is to put the frozen food in right away after you start the oven, before the oven has preheated. Normally what you do for a Bake cycle is wait for the oven to beep once, indicating it has preheated to the desired temperature, then you put your frozen food in. Once the oven beeps at preheat, it starts counting down the time setting. However putting in a significant amount of frozen food can significantly cool down the interior of a toaster oven, although with this oven the displayed temperature never changes. It can take the oven several minutes to come back up to the desired temperature, which doesn\'t give the full amount of cooking because the oven temperature has been low for several minutes. I avoid this problem by putting the frozen food in right away, right after I start the oven, before the preheat beep. Because there\'s a load of frozen food inside, it can take the oven several minutes more than usual to preheat, but when it beeps, the food is already in, and I know the interior temperature is at the full desired value, and that the interior will stay at the full temperature for the full time duration. I think this is a pretty safe way to cook, plus I have an electronic thermometer I can poke into the food to make sure it is hot enough. I have found the included tray and liner to clean up easily. They are not perfectly non-stick, but close enough. Toast comes out pretty nicely using the default setting, but be sure to place the wire rack in the lower slot, facing up. There are actually four different rack positions: upper slot facing up, upper slot facing down, lower slot facing up, and lower slot facing down. To toast the top and bottom of the bread evenly, put the rack in the lower slot, facing up. To tell the truth, as a single guy, I have gone literally years without using a full-size oven. And there are plenty of food items that you really can\'t microwave, they really need to be baked or broiled. Now that I have this toaster oven, though, I use it practically daily because it is so quick and easy and convenient.'),
(1958, 12, 1, 1, '2016-06-23', 'Very happy! I am very happy with my Toastation. The toaster is wide enough for muffins and sliced toast breads. The oven works well for small items, saves large oven costs. Very happy with small compact size, looks good also!'),
(1959, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'Amazing coffee like no other Amazing coffee like no other. I just wish the Whole Foods coffee pods worked with it. But anyhow still amazing! Color LED display is cool too!'),
(1960, 4, 1, 4, '2016-04-24', 'Perfect size. The only thing we (and our dogs) ... Perfect size. The only thing we (and our dogs) don\'t like is the screeching buzzer when the toast is done.'),
(1961, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-05', 'wow Works great for the price'),
(1962, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-09', 'I love it. Finally....a coffee carafe that doesn\'t dribble.  I have gone through 15 coffee makers looking for one that doesn\'t drip all over the counter when you pour it.  I love it.'),
(1963, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-20', 'FIRE HAZARD FIRE HAZARD!  I bought one of these on Jan 9, 2015 and wasn\'t all that thrilled with it to start with. Making toast was difficult as the distance on the dial between \"barley warmed\" and \"burnt to a crisp\" is so short that it\'s a guess every time as to where to set it and you either ended up restarting it 2 or 3 times to get \"toast\" instead of bread or having it so burnt you had to throw it out and start over. I was considering bringing it back but got busy with other things and hadn\'t gotten around to it yet. THEN, the other night, my 17 year old son was making a piece of toast when the bread burst into flames inside the oven! Fortunately, he was nearby and noticed smoke coming from the oven fairly quickly so no damage was done - either to the house or the oven BUT had he gone off somewhere to do something else there COULD have been damage - and it COULD have been serious. Since I cannot trust that with 4 (or more) people using this toaster, that no one will EVER put in a piece of bread and walk away and leave it unattended for a few minutes, then I cannot trust having this appliance in my house. Fortunately, the toaster was new enough that I was able to return it to the store so I cannot speak to whether or not Black and Decker\'s customer service is any better than their toasters or not.'),
(1964, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-25', 'Please don\'t believe reviews, poor quality Please don\'t believe reviews, this product is not worth it. Every time I use this blender it splashes/leaks the fluid through the cap.'),
(1965, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'I am the purchaser of all items, but not ... I am the purchaser of all items, but not always the user. I am only aware if there is a problem, if someone complains. There was no complaint on this item.'),
(1966, 9, 1, 1, '2016-01-20', 'lukewarm brown water - just what I wanted! Ugh, what a waste of time and money! I spent a lot of time reading reviews, even into page 10, to decide whether or not to go with the on-demand or with a classic Bunn. I wanted a coffee maker with a timer and one that could make a comparable brew to that of my manual pour-over method. This machine could do nothing of the sort on any level! Even after adjusting water, adjusting settings, adjusting amount of grounds as well as the grind itself, it still made the worst coffee. I think my $14.99 Mr. Coffee couldn\'t destroy quality beans like this one did! I\'ve had it two days, I attempted brews 3 times a day to absolute dissatisfaction. I should have taken more account on the other reviewers which will have similar complaints to mine: - the coffee was NEVER \"piping hot\" - not even close! Not during, at or after brewing. At the end of the shut off time? The coffee was barely even warm , after sitting there for two hours over the heat unit?! Unacceptable. I use exactly 2 tbsp of half n half to 4c of coffee - because the coffee was never hot after brewing, the coffee certainly wasn\'t hot after I put my half n half in it. Thanks, but no thanks. - the coffee was just GROSS. I\'ve never been so annoyed at having to use my locally roasted beans in order to find a way for this machine to make a brew that was full-bodied and kept the taste of the roast honest. I used every setting - 1-4 c and regular, I used just the gold filter, I used just a paper filter, I used both the paper filter in the gold filter, I adjusted the grind from fine-medium, medium, medium coarse, I measured out exactly the same amount of coffee (and water) that I use every day and couldn\'t replicate the brew with this machine. Just gross. Watery. Bitter. No depth. You name it, nothing decent about what was extracted out of some really great beans (that I have been preparing and drinking for months!) came out of any brew cycle that I attempted with this unit. - the coffee gauge quit today (on the second day), and as others mentioned, it was pretty hokey, fairly inaccurate, and thus, not very useful for its intention - it\'s profile is HUGE, be prepared to find a way to find space for it on the counters, and no, you can\'t open up the lid with wall cupboards, you have to pull the unit out, push it back in, blah blah blah - first world problem for sure, but, it\'s huge and that could be a detraction to many. - that cord thing that everyone is talking about? The struggle is real. I read about it before I bought it and I thought I was immune/informed. When I rec\'d the unit, I went to pull on the cord to get more cordage out as many reviewers mentioned. No go. I pulled more. I pulled to a point where I thought I might break it and then I went back to reviews...and spent another half hour digging through reviews to find out if I was crazy or not. In the end, I went back to the unit and I completely REEFED on the stupid cord and it finally came free. Why this has to be the case is pretty annoying - and you could easily send the whole machine flying if you didn\'t have it bolted down, the way you have use so much force to yank that stupid cord out! - the removable water tank? Another ergonomic/usefulness miss - You can\'t see what you\'re putting in there unless you tip it up towards you in the sink - which makes the water level at an angle, and thus, immeasurable. So, you have to set it down on the counter, wait for water to level, see if you hit the mark, go back under the faucet..back and forth, back and forth. About that high profile? My sink isn\'t very big - but thankfully I have a high arching faucet - otherwise, getting water into that tank from the sink/faucet would be even more obnoxious. By day two, I just filled my coffee mug with the water I needed and poured it into the water reservoir while it was still attached to the unit. It\'s pointless to remove the water reservoir to fill it. You\'ll see what I mean the first time you fill it and want a specific water level. - the on-demand pour was slow, just slow, obnoxious...the handle that you push down seemed like it required much more force than seemed necessary. The light? Hokey. Really, who needs a light? You can SEE how much coffee you\'re putting in your cup. Just LOOK at your cup - since you have to stand there for five minutes with your finger on the pour button while you\'re waiting for 8 oz to dribble out..... - the clock setting buttons: wow, like others, I thought they were broken! They don\'t push in/out by much, they\'re not responsive AT ALL, after you\'ve braced the machine from the back with one hand while trying to mash down the hour or minute button to get it to scroll up or down. Seems like something rudimentary as far as mechanics and interface go, but, another \"cheap\" feature on this expensive machine - speaking of \"cheap\" - I had a Hamilton Beach version what seems like a 100 years ago (probably about 7) that was as you would expect a HB machine to be - sort of good looking, but not stainless, mostly plastic, full-featured, and medium expectations of workability and brew. Well, this $100 stainless Cuisinart surrounded by plastic and cheap gimmicky plastic features is hands down far worse than any HB machine I\'ve ever owned. The HB had a viewable tank (to see how much you had left), not a crappy inaccurate hokey \"dial\", it has an easy push and fast fill on-demand system, it had the time/clock/programmable features, it made a decent cup of coffee, and it made it HOT, kept it HOT, it was worth it\'s $40 and performed about 110% better than this abomination did. - I\'ve been awake every morning at 6am, hoping it would be the day that I made this coffee machine work/make a good cup of coffee, but instead, spent the last half hour writing this review now that I have it packaged up in the return box and waiting for UPS to come pick it up. Just a total joke of a coffee maker. I should have known better - simple is better when it comes to coffee and I\'ll just go back to my simple pour over brewing method. No more gadgets, no matter how novel or what they\'re dressed up in, or, what their brand name is. Sad. As many others stated, \"I really wanted it to work.\"'),
(1967, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-27', 'Five Stars works well and heats fast'),
(1968, 5, 1, 2, '2016-07-09', 'Unexpected problem Sent it back after 3 days and ordered a known coffee maker that I had previously ordered on Amazon. The carafe consistently retained condensation which wouldn\'t dry up. Every pour was preceded by a quantity of this condensation before the coffee would pour. Tried several pots and the problem wouldn\'t go away. Also, never knew how much coffee was in the carafe because the condensation blocked any visibility.. Other than that, it worked great and the price was right.'),
(1969, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-12', 'Great oven. Perfect for us. Works great as a toaster, if you\'re not in a hurry, and better as an oven.  We love using it.'),
(1970, 8, 1, 4, '2016-03-22', 'Perfect coffeepot. Perfect serving size for one or two persons. Keeps coffee at perfect warming temperature after perked.'),
(1971, 5, 1, 4, '2015-11-27', 'Four Stars Luv it keeps coffe hot n easy to fill too'),
(1972, 3, 1, 2, '2016-03-22', 'It works just fine. But I purchased this as a replacement for the same model I bought 6-ish years ago. It works just fine. But, the construction is flimsy. I burned my hand on the top of the piece, the construction is clearly lower quality of their previous models. The feel of the buttons are low quality, the drawers don\'t fit well, and this model comes with fewer accessories. I should have kept the older model.'),
(1973, 4, 1, 2, '2015-07-26', 'Great... until it dies from a known defect Bottom elements warp and die.  They are non-replaceable so you have to replace the whole unit.  Up until it died, I was quite happy with it.  Sadly, Cuisinart\'s reputation took a ding with this oven, especially considering they haven\'t fixed the issue and are selling an oven with a known issue.'),
(1974, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Five Stars Operates great just as advertised.'),
(1975, 11, 1, 3, '2014-03-14', 'Good size -- but ignites toast Clean lines, compact and easy to use, but even on lowest setting toast is dark; had toast ignite and smoke up the house on medium setting. We bought a different toaster to replace'),
(1976, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', '... brew a small amount that would taste just as good as a whole pot Had been searching for a coffee pot that would brew a small amount that would taste just as good as a whole pot, use the 1-4 cup brew for mornings, and the bold in the afternoon (brew even smaller amounts), and both brew perfect. I don\'t brew a large pot unless I have company, (5 cups mornings & 3 cups afternoons) give my spouse and I just the right amount of coffee for 1 mug each in the AM, and about 3/4 cup in the afternoon and yet gives the taste of a full brewed pot. Our previous coffee maker did not have the options and we only had GOOD coffee when brewing a full pot. Now I have the best of both full and small. Would recommend this pot. Easy clean up too.'),
(1977, 8, 1, 1, '2016-07-19', 'Doesn\'t work! It doesn\'t heat the water. Don\'t buy this it is a rip off.'),
(1978, 5, 1, 4, '2014-01-08', 'Compact and fairly easy to use Works well, achieves the purpose. I would\'ve liked the item to have the filter accessory as an option. I believe it improves the taste of the coffee.'),
(1979, 12, 1, 4, '2016-12-11', 'Four Stars nice product.  fast shipping.'),
(1980, 2, 1, 4, '2015-06-03', 'It is good. i love it and it\'s easy to It is good.i love it and it\'s easy to clean'),
(1981, 6, 1, 4, '2015-04-08', 'Four Stars Does the job at the higher setting (4 and above). Lower settings don\'t really work well.'),
(1982, 6, 1, 4, '2014-07-27', 'Great Toaster! I\'ve never had a toaster that I liked, until now.  They\'ve always been disappointing.  Until now.  I bought this Cuisinart model in red and it looks so nice and performs above my expectations.  Am very happy that I got this.'),
(1983, 10, 1, 4, '2015-06-06', 'A must-have in our house with people who loves shakes ... A must-have in our house with people who loves shakes too much. Really affordable and it\'s still functional up to now.'),
(1984, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Very Satisfied Customer After using a Keurig machine at my job for 2 weeks I decided to buy one. I was very impressed at how good a cup of coffee it brewed. The one I used at work was a more expensive one but brews the same as the home version one I bought. Since it\'s my first Keurig I still have some time to go to run into any problems if any. I still don\'t see the drawback of using Keurig\'s K cups being that all in all I still save time and money than having to drive and buy my cups of coffee at the nearest coffee shop. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(1985, 9, 1, 3, '2016-08-11', 'Great coffee maker Great coffee maker, but the grinds are all over the basket and the top.  Pain to clean.  I tried using less water and coffee, but still the same.  I had this coffee maker about 3 years ago and never had this problem. I guess products are getting worse instead of better.'),
(1986, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'Amazing product! Totally worth it! Love this Keurig ! Perfect for college and gatherings with friends ! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(1987, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-04', 'Five Stars Perfect for the camper,  works great and easy to use.'),
(1988, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'Simple and easy to use This is as close to the old simple push-button start Black & Decker toaster oven as you can get.  It took a while to get used to remembering that now there are 2 knobs that have to be turned to \"toast\" or \"bake\" when you change settings, but once you get used to that overall it\'s pretty simple to use and toasts quickly, which is what we wanted.  Houseguests can sort out how to toast their bread in the morning or bake a frozen pizza at midnight on their own without waking you up to get a tutorial, very important.  The removable crumb tray is a great improvement, makes it easy to keep the bottom clean.  Toasts and bakes evenly.  We use it every day multiple times per day for toasting, baking, and reheating,  and are truly delighted.  A relief since most toaster ovens we looked at are so complicated, and we wanted a simple one without any bells or whistles.'),
(1989, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-20', 'It is nice looking, and the swing out basket and removable ... I looked at coffee makers for a while before deciding on this one. It is nice looking, and the swing out basket and removable tank make this a winner. The coffee it makes is good. My advice is to skip the \"bold\" feature when using it at first. It doesn\'t seem to make tons of difference once the pot is done, but the first 2 cups are jet fuel.'),
(1990, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-06', 'ehhhh.....smh Worked great for bout a month and not1 but2 both stop working at the same time. I thought my ppower outlets went out.. but nope. The blenders both took a crap... smh'),
(1991, 2, 1, 1, '2016-05-19', 'CAUGHT ON FIRE!!!!!!!!! Keep a fire extinguisher handy if you are going to use this toaster oven. I believe this is my first product review on Amazon. I really felt the need to post a review though because this thing caught on fire! I just started toasting some corn shells and the toaster oven started smoking. The shells weren\'t even lightly brown. I opened the door and a huge ball of fire shot out. I closed it quickly, but by then, fire was coming out of the cracks in the door. I ended up having to use a fire extinguisher to put it out (first time I\'ve ever needed on in my 47 years of life). As you can see in the photo, the taco shells ended up a bit overdone after being roasted in a giant fire. The best I could tell, the heating element itself was what caught fire (the bar in the back of the toaster that turns read when cooking). Oh yeah, cleaning up after a fire extinguisher is a big pain in the booty. The stuff goes everywhere.'),
(1992, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-22', 'Five Stars I recommend a reseller'),
(1993, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-18', 'It\'s a great little toaster oven It\'s a great little toaster oven. I would have given it 5 stars but to toast something, you have to set all 3 controls.  The first two to \"Toast\" and the third to how dark or light you want it toasted.'),
(1994, 8, 1, 5, '2014-12-22', 'Nice, simple little coffee maker... Nice little coffee maker.  I had a 12 cup maker and found myself making and drinking too much coffee.  This one works well, is the perfect size for 2 to 2-1/2 cups of morning coffee or a couple cups after dinner.  The smaller size seems to make a stronger, better tasting cup of coffee.  It\'s simple, easy to use and does not keep trying to pump water when the reservoir is empty like my old one did (drove the wife crazy).');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(1995, 9, 1, 4, '2015-04-26', 'Its a drip coffee pot they are all pretty comparable in how the coffee tastes Let me start buy saying I am a Iron Worker ;-) What dose that have to do with a coffee pot review absolutely nothing just wanted to follow suit. I just got the coffee pot It seems to make the coffee a tad hotter then the brew station but not to hot. Its a drip coffee pot they are all pretty comparable in how the coffee tastes. My brew station lasted not quite a year then it started making only half a pot then I had to restart it to get it to finish a full pot. The Brew station also started leaking water under the reservoir. So at double the price If this lasts 2 years Ill be happy. I like the light above the cup ,and after using it I like the hand operated dependence switch over the cup activated one in the brew station. now we just have to wait 2 years and see if it holds up.'),
(1996, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Love my Keurig! Very happy with my Keurig.  Easy to use and quick to prepare.  Great variety of coffees to choose from.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.  It helped me choose several great flavors!  No real clean up involved.  Love to be able to make coffee for more than just 1 with the carafe.'),
(1997, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'Five Stars 5 star'),
(1998, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-21', 'Five Stars Great quality. Works well.'),
(1999, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-24', 'Love this oven! this toaster oven is the perfect size and design! I had the model before it for 4 years and the only reason I ordered a new one was because it was looking rough. For the price it is a great buy!'),
(2000, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-24', 'super fast, super simple Quick to make pot of coffee. Pot is 25oz., i get three 8 oz cups, which works for me.  Plastic taste is gone after 2or 3 pots. This is s super fast, super simple ( nothing automatic,  only control is on off switch) survival coffee brewing, just the way i like it.'),
(2001, 12, 1, 4, '2014-01-31', 'Looks good on the counter It is really neat looking. I love it. The toaster over itself is smaller than a normal oven, so you need to be aware of that before you buy it. My daughter does NOT like hers but I love mine.'),
(2002, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-01', 'Love it. Make perfect toast Love it. Make perfect toast. And the oven is great for smal sandwich and pizza. The color are a very nice red'),
(2003, 6, 1, 4, '2015-12-23', 'four star Good looking product at good price'),
(2004, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-27', 'it\'s perfect, and I can just take it and go I use it so much, it\'s perfect, and I can just take it and go.'),
(2005, 5, 1, 4, '2016-10-05', 'Decent coffee maker I like that the water reservoir removes. Don\'t like that there is no alarm for when the coffee finishes brewing or that the 2hr. timer has run out.'),
(2006, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-22', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(2007, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-08', 'Exactly what I wanted Exactly what I wanted. Excellent quality product.'),
(2008, 12, 1, 5, '2016-01-15', 'I love this little toaster I love this little toaster. It does exactly what it\'s supposed to do and the best part is that it doesn\'t take up too much valuable work space!'),
(2009, 2, 1, 2, '2015-10-23', 'Could be great unit for the money, if only..... Toaster ovens are pretty simple and have been around a long time, one would think someone would get it right. This one actually makes toast pretty well, along with the other things a small toaster oven does, and is reasonably priced - that\'s the good part. Bad part is the controls- there are three almost identical knobs that all have to be turned to the correct  spot to toast, bake, broil, whatever. If you have one in the wrong place, well, things don\'t work as expected. The icons are pretty small too, so you have to look closely  to make sure  you you\'ve chosen bake instead of broil and such. In addition, the timer ( bottom ) knob, which as normal turns to the right to set the time, and toast darkness- no problem there. But if you want to finish early, you naturally just  want to turn the knob all the way to the left- there\'s the problem, all the way to the left puts it into \"always on\" mode, and there\'s no good feel where that happens. You have to find the exact spot between timer and on to turn it off. AND opening the door doesn\'t turn it off either. I could see this as a safety hazard, you could easily leave the oven on all day. Just a little better thinking would turn this into a \"best buy\". As specific solution, 4  buttons for toast, broil, bake and warm could take the place of the middle knob, and the toast button could override the toast setting on the top knob,  it\'s redundant. As is, you get what you pay for.'),
(2010, 8, 1, 4, '2016-01-01', 'Four Stars Good deal wish it had a way to be able to brew and pour with auto turn off'),
(2011, 6, 1, 2, '2014-04-28', 'Lacks completely toasting evenly  my 4 bakery sliced bread. It requires additional time to toast 4 slices of bread and being untimed, over toasts bread. Somewhat better than the new Calphalon 4 slot toaster.'),
(2012, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-15', 'Here\'s a Toast... Preforms well on all levels...'),
(2013, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Best coffee maker ever! I love my new Keurig! I had the small one cup version, unfortunately it died after 5 years of use. I really like having a water tank. Not having to fill for each cup is a plus. Additionally, it brews really fast. Not only that but it brews a great cup of coffee. Every time, exactly the same. Can\'t beat it. And with a variety of cups to use, I will never get bored. Great product. Can\'t recommend it enough. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2014, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-28', 'GREAT DRIP COFFEE MAKER GREAT PRODUCT GOOD PRICE FAST SHIPPING'),
(2015, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-19', 'Five Stars Worked great! Perfectly met needs.'),
(2016, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-05', 'Coffee Lover My husband loves it!  It works well and has his coffee ready and waiting when he wants it!.'),
(2017, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-28', 'Excellent coffee maker for the money Have used it every day since purchase.  Excellent coffee maker for the money.'),
(2018, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Great price. We like it so far Great price.  We like it so far, but we\'ll see how long it lasts.'),
(2019, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-22', 'Defective Heating Element- Happened to me TWICE! I really like this toaster oven for so many reasons BUT this is the second one I have bought and AGAIN the front heating element has arced so high it is nearly touching the oven rack. I thought the first one might have been defective by chance but getting a second one 2 1/2 years later with the same problem seems beyond mere coincidence to me. DON\"T BUY THIS TOASTER OVEN! Obviously Cuisinart knows they are selling a product with this defect and they don\'t care. Because this happened beyond the 1 year warranty, they will not replace it. Also, I found that I cannot get a replacement heating element to fix it! I will have to find another brand to replace it.'),
(2020, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-11', 'Five Stars Good product.'),
(2021, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-12', 'Great coffee maker! Works perfectly...really like the design. Mess free!'),
(2022, 7, 3, 4, '2014-01-13', 'Don\'t have to make a full pot all the time'),
(2023, 11, 1, 3, '2015-04-19', 'Good for heating food but slow at toasting Handy but takes a long time to toast.'),
(2024, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-27', 'Five Stars Good basic coffee maker.  Does its job.  Zero problems in 2 years.'),
(2025, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-11', 'This replacement is excellent. Very nice Finally retired my old B&D toast-r-oven.  This replacement is excellent.  Very nice.  Great controls.  Easy to read.  True 4 slice capacity.'),
(2026, 12, 1, 3, '2014-07-23', 'Works well for what I need. I do find ... Works well for what I need.  I do find I need to keep the oven temp a bit lower than called for in recipes when I am baking or roasting something, otherwise it burns the food.'),
(2027, 3, 1, 4, '2014-12-16', 'Four Stars Works great! Bigger than I expected, but sleek, modern and overall works perfectly!'),
(2028, 11, 1, 4, '2014-05-26', 'Great for the workplace I have the Breville Smart Compact oven for home. For someone who was not willing to sacrifice counter space for a toaster oven, the Breville is well worth it! Lots of features and functionality. That being said, I hesitate to invest that same money in a unit for work. The Black & Decker 4 slice toaster oven is pretty good. It\'s used to reheat leftovers or make toast. Simple and easy with control knobs that are easy to read and understand. It\'s been a great addition to my office and a convenient way to warm up lunch.'),
(2029, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'As Advertized Great coffee maker'),
(2030, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-06', 'Complete Electrical Failure This product had a complete electrical failure after 2months, 3 days.'),
(2031, 9, 1, 3, '2015-09-10', 'Love the coffee pot Love the coffee pot, but it leaks sometimes where the coffee comes out, even thought I clean out the pot every night.I have solved that problem by keeping an cup under the spout when not getting coffee.'),
(2032, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'Easy in the kitchen Very user friendly.'),
(2033, 6, 1, 4, '2014-07-31', 'It\'s light weight. It toasts and there are no ... It\'s light weight.  It toasts and there are no hot spots on the outside that are dangerous.'),
(2034, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-18', 'the coffee is excellent & so nice to have a fresh cup in ... the coffee is excellent & so nice to have a fresh cup in minutes instead of waiting for a whole pot to brew.'),
(2035, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-02', 'compacked Very compacked, sets just right on my counter.'),
(2036, 3, 1, 1, '2016-03-24', 'Disappointed...inaccurate temperatures I wanted to like this oven.  I liked the size, design, the controls were relatively easy to use.  I liked everything about it BUT the temperature was completely inaccurate.  The first thing I baked took over twice as long, so I tested it with an oven thermometer, even bought another one in case the old one I had was inaccurate and found at a high temperate, 450, it was about 75 to 100 degrees lower depending on the thermometer I used.  It was less off at lower temperatures.  I used the over for nearly a week and tested the temperate for several days.  I then pulled out my old, no name, $12 smaller toaster oven that this one replaced and found it  15 degrees different from the 450 setting, so it was more accurate. I\'m really disappointed and decided to not try another Black and Decker and instead am trying a different brand.'),
(2037, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-27', 'This is perfect for me This is perfect for me.  I have a small kitchen, and I like the options to use as a toaster or a mini oven.  Great product!'),
(2038, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-19', 'Five Stars Arrived as described and works as described.  Makes coffee Fast!'),
(2039, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-28', 'One Star Wouldn\'t even chop baby spinach'),
(2040, 4, 1, 2, '2015-10-30', 'Problem with lower front heating element, reported to Consumer Products Safety Commision as unsafe We purchased this item from a retail store in 2012 and noticed earlier this year that the lower front heating element was slightly warped. This element is now distorted inwards for about 2 inches and we have unplugged it due to our concern that it may break and create a hazard. We have contacted Cuisinart and they are willing to replace it if we send in the power cord and cover the shipping and handling (just like other reviewers had mentioned). However, they did not response to our inquiry about why this is happening or if it is still safe to use. We are reluctant to have this replaced. After reading the comments by other reviewers on Amazon, we have reported this problem to the Consumer Products Safety Commission on-line at [...] I suggest other users to do the same if they feel that this product is unsafe.'),
(2041, 6, 1, 3, '2015-04-05', 'Overall quality seems great but toasts one side of each slice of bread ... Overall quality seems great but toasts one side of each slice of bread considerably more than the other. Not so bad that I would return the toaster but I expected a little more consistency.'),
(2042, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-18', 'Love this. Only problem was the top plate broke ... Love this. Only problem was the top plate broke off and kept falling off. A little glue and it\'s good to go and you would never know.'),
(2043, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-09', 'Perfect for work! Got this for work. Love it! It works great!.'),
(2044, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-27', 'Five Stars excellent'),
(2045, 5, 1, 1, '2014-02-08', 'INADIQUITE DESCRIPTION I AM A A DISABLED VET 100%V DISABILITY AND I HAVE NO USE OF MY RIGHT ARM.  IT WAS SEVERED IN COMBAT.  I ORDERED THIS UNIT BECAUSE OF THE STATED EASY OPEN DESIGN.  WHAT WAS NOT DISCLOSED IS THAT THERE IS A BUTTON HALF WAY BACK ON THE RIGHT SIDE THAT NEEDS TO BE PRESSED TO RELEASE THE COFFEE BASKET.  I TRIED TO RETURN THE PRODUCT DESCRIBING MY PROBLEM AND LACK OF INFORMATION IN THE DESCRIPTION BUT WAS REFUSED EVEN THOUGH THE UNIT WAS NOT USED.  I WOULD GIVE THEM A NEGATIVE FIVE IF I COULD.  VERY POOR BUSINESS PRACTICE AND A DIS SERVICE TO ALL DISABLED VETS !!!  TO THIS DAY I STILL HAVE NOT GOTTEN A RETURN AUTHORIZATION EVEN THOUGH I AGREED TO PAY FOR THE SHIPPING AND JUST RETURN UNDER A NO LONGER WANTED  RETURN. I AM UPSET AND HAVE SO MUCH IN MY LIFE TO DEAL WITH AND THIS SHOULD BE A NO BRAINER.  SHAME ON YOU PEOPLE SHAME.......'),
(2046, 6, 1, 2, '2015-10-14', 'Two Stars Horrible horrible! Ruined half loaf of bread.'),
(2047, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-27', 'A winner from Hamilton Beach. Best coffee maker I ever owned, bar none.  Easy to use....easy to fill with water.  Swing out basket makes putting in coffee a snap.  The timer when to start your coffee in the morning and you\'re good to go.  I use bottled water and the coffee is the best I ever had.  Machine has three brewing choices.  I use the \"Regular\" setting.  Love the automatic shut off after two hours.......in case I forget.  Great machine.  I recommend it to anyone needing a coffee maker.'),
(2048, 7, 3, 1, '2014-12-31', 'The coffee leaks out of the pod and makes a mess. It makes a mess. At the end of the brewing process, the machine let out one big belch spewing coffee, water and grounds all over my counter top.'),
(2049, 4, 1, 4, '2016-04-23', 'Four Stars Great oven but shipping took forever'),
(2050, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-28', 'Does not last... One year and one month in, and it\'s broken. Door won\'t open, two rivets have popped off...I would not recommend this product if you\'re looking for durability and longevity.'),
(2051, 3, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'Perfect toast My wife loves it! I probably couldn\'t figure out how to turn it on, but she says its the best she\'s ever used.'),
(2052, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-29', 'Great Design, Easy to Use Had this coffee maker for about three months, it\'s still holding up just fine. Other reviews about the door not closing and heat pad not working scared me off a little but ALL the reviews on coffee makers scare me, a little. This coffee maker is a really great design, in that the back water reservoir detaches for easy fill-up. You don\'t have to fill the coffee pot, then pour it in the machine, although you can if you want. The coffee and filter goes in the front, not on top like most machines. Every little easy time-saver helps when making coffee. You can set the temperature, low medium high. You can also set strength to regular or bold. The program to set it to brew in the morning is totally easy to understand, you won\'t have to reference the instructions forever. The only thing is, it takes a while to brew. But if you\'re setting it to brew while you sleep, who cares? I just hope it can last for more than two years. That seems to be the life span of all coffee makers, these days...'),
(2053, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-23', 'Five Stars Great value, works as well as much higher priced personal blenders.'),
(2054, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-08', 'Five Stars Cooked chicken wings perfectly'),
(2055, 7, 3, 1, '2015-09-16', 'worthless as a pod brewer. tears to big of hole in bottom of pod and coffee grounds come out.'),
(2056, 7, 3, 1, '2015-09-16', 'worthless as a pod brewer. tears to big of hole in bottom of pod and coffee grounds come out.'),
(2057, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'This is great for people who have small kitchens or limited storage ... This is great for people who have small kitchens or limited storage space. Single serving use. My husband loves it for making milkshakes and cab drink right from it. Can\'t beat the price.'),
(2058, 8, 1, 2, '2016-03-25', 'It\'s a leaker. I have been using this coffeemaker for a bit over a month each morning. Lately I have noticed a pool of water accumulating on the countertop at its base. Today I filled the carafe to the 5 cup level w/o coffee in the basket to validate the leakage. There must be a design flaw. It leaked despite my care operating the unit. My conclusion is that it is not worth saving a couple of bucks to purchase this low-end leaky coffeemaker.'),
(2059, 5, 1, 2, '2015-04-02', 'Not HOT ENOUGH! I rate a coffee pot on just how hot it brews and keeps my coffee, especially when you add a little cream it should not cool it off to where it is just lukewarm but this coffee maker did. I am definitely disappointed because all the reviews spoke highly but I have to microwave every cup I drink whether with cream or not!'),
(2060, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-18', 'Five Stars When my well used GE coffee maker finally bit the dust, I searched Amazon for a suitable replacement.  I stumbled on this coffee maker and I am so happy.  Detachable water resivoir and swing out basket!  Easy, brews good coffee and easy clean up. I did add the gold tone basket to strain out the coffee grounds. Highly recommend'),
(2061, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-01', 'Five Stars As expected and fast delivery'),
(2062, 5, 1, 3, '2016-01-06', 'Good, Hot, Coffee The good: this coffee maker makes 12 cups of good hot coffee. The programming function is simple. The hot plate keeps coffee hot for plenty of time. I like the ability to remove the water pitcher for cleaning or refilling. Also the carafe pours perfectly with no dripping down the side. The bad: the casing around the buttons and clock broke off after only two weeks. That casing is not supposed to be removable at all. Luckily, no visible damage and a bit of super glue and all is right again. But, I think it does show a bit of the product quality that something like that broke within such a short period of time. That said, I\'ve used this daily for roughly 3 months now and everything else has held up perfectly.'),
(2063, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-09', 'It\'s is both fun and delicious I got this because I couldn\'t use the oven. It works magic! I obviously cannot bake or toast things that are too big, but I was able to make mini pies and pastries in here. It\'s is both fun and delicious. I have had it for a while now, and it is holding strong as ever. ___'),
(2064, 4, 1, 1, '2015-07-10', 'Hazardous The unit worked great - until I received an electrical shock upon pushing the start button.  I contacted their customer service and they had an extremely lackadaisical attitude about something that is potentially hazardous. I was hoping to exchange it for a new unit, but no such luck.  After numerous email exchanges over a period of weeks, they said someone would call me.  No one ever called. In contrast, I recently purchased an LG blue tooth headset.  After 3 months the unit developed a problem.  I got on a chat window and within 10 minutes they processed a return for me.  Maybe I should look for an LG toaster.'),
(2065, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-25', 'Solid Toaster Oven In the 2 weeks since I\'ve received it, it\'s been working very well - much better than the Waring toaster oven. It has less control knobs, but gets the job done. It toasts bread much more evenly than the Waring as well.'),
(2066, 10, 1, 3, '2015-01-03', 'I like it but I ordered it twice and the blender ... I like it but I ordered it twice and the blender broke once before I finally have one working.'),
(2067, 8, 1, 4, '2016-05-02', 'Works fine. Works fine but is a little on the slow side. Good price.'),
(2068, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-19', 'Five Stars An excellent product - good value for the money.'),
(2069, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-09', 'Five Stars Love this thing. Use it almost every day.'),
(2070, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-01', 'Five Stars Nice design and fits right on the little kitchen counter.'),
(2071, 3, 1, 2, '2014-12-03', 'Disappointed. I bought this to replace an almost identical ... Disappointed. I bought this to replace an almost identical black and decker toaster oven that just broke.  I had only had it a couple months and buttons started sticking. The only reason I bought the same one again was bc I needed the same size and had to put it in the same spot. Well this is almost the same model except the cord is several inches shorter. We\'ll my fault as the saying goes \"fool me once....\" Never again will I purchase a black and decker appliance'),
(2072, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-06', 'large size... works well... ... large size... works well... exactly as described... i had the last version of it for 10 years... i didn\'t clean it as much as i should have and i barely took care of it, but it still lasted 10 years... the only reason it died was because i spilled and burned food on the heating parts so it was my fault... but it is high quality and works really well and lasts a long time.. i plan to take care of this one ;-)'),
(2073, 3, 1, 4, '2014-10-31', 'Four Stars I like it.'),
(2074, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'Five Stars Great product. Used daily. Easy to use, clean and store.'),
(2075, 4, 1, 1, '2015-05-20', 'They sould recall this product. DO NOT BUY THIS. Beware of this product. Like many customer\'s pictures, my 2 year old oven\'s heating element got split and bended. I called customer service, they said \"Just throw it away and buy new one cause it\'s out of warranty\" DO NOT BUY THIS.'),
(2076, 12, 1, 3, '2016-07-24', 'Its ok It is ok.  It doesn\'t hold temperature very well so even if you pre heat, the coils will always be on.'),
(2077, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'This Hamilton Beach system is hands down the best I have ever seen I have owned many coffee makers, some very expensive.  This Hamilton Beach system is hands down the best I have ever seen.'),
(2078, 10, 1, 2, '2015-01-18', 'don\'t waste your will only mix soft items. can not put in frozen cubed fruit or berries. does noy blend well.  don\'t waste your money'),
(2079, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-04', 'All One Could Ask for in a Toaster/Convection/Bake oven! This is the first toaster oven I have used in about 30 years; amazed at the upgraded technology!  I received it in a timely fashion. And it was packed very professionally and tightly in great condition on arrival.  The instructions were printed in very small print but I was able to read them with a magnifying glass.  It was a straightforward set-up.  My first use was to bake muffins -- they turned out perfectly on the bake setting.  I next made toast; that, too was perfect.  I will use this little toaster convection oven on a regular basis for small quantity  baking.  It will be a power saver over the big stove oven.  It appears very well made and does not take up too much room on my countertop.  I have not yet tried the convection feature but it suggests a lower temperature setting for convection which will give faster cooking.  I am very pleased with this purchase!'),
(2080, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-09', 'Downgraded one star This is my third Black & Decker toaster oven (they do die after a while). Obviously I like them or I wouldn\'t keep buying them, but I\'ve deducted a star from this iterations for two reasons. The first is that it comes with a tray that is much smaller than the interior of the oven - how much more would it have cost for a full size tray? The second, and more important to me, is that the grill doesn\'t slide open when you open the door as it did in previous versions, meaning you have to reach in for your finished food. I wish my old one hadn\'t died.'),
(2081, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-08', 'Good toaster, good price. Good toaster at a good price.  It was a little smaller than my previous one but it heats up faster.  I can now make toast at the same time it takes me to fry an egg (I used to have to start the toast earlier).  I don\'t think I needed one bigger than this anyways, so I am happy with my purchase.'),
(2082, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-03', 'works great fits bagels with ease works great fits bagels with ease. like the way you can use the lever to lift the toast or bagel up to get it out easier.'),
(2083, 10, 1, 1, '2015-09-29', '3 New Blenders Died in 2 Weeks. Don\'t waste your money. 3 new blenders have broken in 2 weeks. 2 broke on the first use. It runs for a a few minutes, begins to smoke, then the motor dies.  I kept exchanging for a new one b/c it was the only budget blender available, but after the third burnt motor-I visited a different store to purchase a different brand. I had this model a few years ago and it was a good blender. Obviously Hamilton Beach\'s quality has reduced since then.  In fact, this is the 3rd bad experience I\'ve had w/ HB appliances this year. (Well.. actually the 5th if you count all 3 blenders.)'),
(2084, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-12', 'Great appliance This is a really great appliance. It works great and we love it.'),
(2085, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'LOVE this brewer! I love this brewer.  I purchased the brewer for my classroom and it is perfect.  I love the fun purple color.  It is the perfect brewer for my needs. I can brew one cup for busy mornings or I can brew a full carafe when needed.  I have a keurig at home and I HAD to have one at work, too. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(2086, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-20', 'nice toaster oven Wife likes it and I do too. Delivered quickly. 3 months of use and no problems. Nice for a toaster oven.'),
(2087, 3, 1, 3, '2015-07-02', 'I think it\'s a good value if it lasts two years This toaster oven does what it claims to do.  You do have to experiment to see what settings to use for toast, english muffins, etc. It does bake consistently in accord with temperatures called for in recipes.  The controls are not the easiest to use; my wife still hasn\'t mastered the timer after two years of use. Also, it does get quite hot on top, back and front.  When I bought it it came with a 1 year warranty.  It lasted exactly two years before the top element burned out.  This is the 3rd toaster oven I\'ve bought.  The first was a GE toaster oven that was a predecessor of the Black & Decker four slice toaster oven; it lasted close to 10 years, the last two have been a 4 slice and a 6 slice B & D.  The 4 slice one came with a 2 year warranty and the top element burned out just after the 2 year warranty was up.  So I guess I was lucky with the 6 slice model.  Considering the price, I think it\'s a good value if it lasts two years, but don\'t expect it to last longer than that.'),
(2088, 8, 1, 2, '2016-02-22', 'Can I warm that up for you? I pour out a cup right after it\'s brewed and the cup is only warm. Plus I get up bad smell from the unit and the coffee just doesn\'t taste good. I made a mistake and should of got one with a warming carafe.'),
(2089, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-01', 'Great Coffee Maker Great coffee maker.  Love the programmable controls, removable water tank and easy access basket.  I no longer have to pull the whole coffee pot out from under the cabinet to fill it.'),
(2090, 3, 1, 4, '2016-05-01', 'works better. works very well, so much better that my previous unit.'),
(2091, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-28', 'Great even toast with a short 3 prong cord. this is an amazing toaster oven. I\'ve used several different toasters and toaster ovens in my life and this one yields the most even toast. Whether I\'m toasting bagels or sliced bread both sides come out even and I don\'t need to worry about where on the rack I need to align the food. The broiling feature is nice and it bakes evenly as well. The thing I do not like about the toaster is that it does not have a bottom that opens to easily clean out the crumbs on the bottom. Instead they give you an insert to put in the bottom that comes out - but without a bottom hatch this can get messy. One thing to note: this toaster oven has a 3 prong power cord that is very short. It\'s made short so you do not trip over it or cause any injury from an untidy cable. If you need to use an extension cord like I do it\'s a good idea to find one with 3 prongs as well. Without the proper grounding the toaster could be dangerous in the event of a short.'),
(2092, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-19', 'Hand off my perfect coffee pot. This coffee pot is perfect for the guy like myself that wants 2 large cups of coffee every morning and afternoon.'),
(2093, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-10', 'Good Basic Toaster Oven 4.5 stars My long lived toaster finally failed after many years. I decided to replace it with a toaster oven. I do not make toast often, but when you want toast, you want it. My son has a toaster oven his family uses frequently. I decided to peruse the Amazon toaster oven reviews, and I found this toaster oven to be the most reviewed and best liked. The toaster oven came well packaged and easy to unpack. There are two quick use pamphlets, one in English, French, and Spanish. The directional pamphlet I  found wanting. It gives good directions on the parts of the toaster oven, how to make toast, and the assorted trays. However, there is no information on baking, how long a food might take etc. There are four modes, warm, bake, broil and toast. I have made toast several times to try it out, and this toaster is quite nice. I like medium brown toast and set the knob where that mode might be. I was correct, nicely browned toast. I wanted to brown the top of a cheese dish and used the broiler, I watched carefully, and it broiled to my satisfaction. This toaster oven is a good size for my kitchen. A 2 foot long 3 prong plug. The instructions recommend leaving the toaster oven unplugged until you use it. The toast crack and trays I hand washed before using, and will hand wash when needed. For the price, I think this is a good basic toaster oven. No big bells and whistles, but it has all you might need. Recommended. prisrob 03-10-16'),
(2094, 4, 1, 1, '2015-04-24', 'One Star BEWARE.......MADE IN CHINA'),
(2095, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Five Stars Great buy fast shipping.'),
(2096, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-09', 'Love it A little better than the older model without the light.  Really like using this machine.'),
(2097, 6, 1, 4, '2015-06-26', 'Toaster is good. I have only used it a few times. Just got it a week ago and I\'m having a little trouble getting the right toast setting. It shouldn\'t be that difficult and it doesn\'t seem too toast too evenly. The outside gets a little warmer that I want, but, overall, I think it will be a good buy! Every Cuisinart appliance that I have had has been a good one.'),
(2098, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-20', 'Five Stars Love the control knobs, the size, and the easy cleanup'),
(2099, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Five Stars very good, it\'s a toaster!'),
(2100, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', '... surpassed my expectations by cooking my food so much better than my previous toaster oven (Frigidaire This oven has surpassed my expectations by cooking my food so much better than my previous toaster oven (Frigidaire, stopped working after 2 years) and my previous apartment gas oven that I almost didn\'t recognize my usual recipes!  I mainly use it to replace the gas oven for smaller items so I don\'t know how well it toasts or broils, but using the bake mode has been spectacularly successful.  I also cannot comment on how long it lasts since I have only had it several weeks. If you like to make smaller items like meatloaf or casseroles then you are in for a real treat!'),
(2101, 5, 1, 4, '2014-11-17', 'Works great so far! Got this coffee maker a few weeks ago after having 3 Mr Coffee programmable units go bad in 2 1/2 yrs. Does the job quickly, actually has a no-drip coffee pot, easy to use and set, easy to read display.  We also like the variable temperature of the warming plate...keeps the coffee from getting stale too fast.  I must admit that we do not use the detachable water resevoir feature...my hubby is nervous that it will start leaking.  Hope it continues to perform for a long time.'),
(2102, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-04', 'My wife uses this every morning to make her breakfast ... My wife uses this every morning to make her breakfast drink.  Works very well.  I would prefer that the blade be removable for cleaning.'),
(2103, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-01', 'Broke after 30 days Broke after 30 days and the support was bad.'),
(2104, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-19', 'Great value. Love it. All the features of the really pricey models at a reasonable price.'),
(2105, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'This was the greatest gift. It is so easy to use and ... This was the greatest gift.  It is so easy to use and clean, and the coffee brews perfectly.  We love it.  It has an automatic shut off, which helps a great deal.  My husband gets it ready in the evening, and it turns itself on in the morning, and brews our coffee.  We have had other brands, but this is the easiest, and the best one we\'ve had so far.'),
(2106, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-24', 'Breakfast has never been better Four slots in one toaster - genius. Making toast in the morning for the kids is so simple, and we get the perfect browned bread every single time. Definitely buy this if you\'re in the market for a toaster, it\'s the best I\'ve ever used!'),
(2107, 1, 1, 1, '2015-09-11', 'Disappointed Despite using Keurig for years, I am so disappointed in this machine after two days of ownership, I may well return it. Can I give it a negative star?  Despite running about 15 cups of just water through it I can still taste a chemical, plasticy very unpleasant flavor. The off button icon doesn\'t work, so I have to pull the plug to shut it off. After brewing it drips for quite a while, unlike my two other Keurig machines. There is no way to set the default cup size. I have to program it for 6 oz from it\'s own default of 8 oz every time. The noises it makes are an embarrassment. If I can\'t clear the terrible flavor by tomorrow I will return it. When I called Keurig\'s customer service number they harassed me for all sorts of information rather than helping me even though I bought this machine through them on my membership points. They left me on hold for 10 minutes so I hung up. I drink over $100/month of Keurig coffee, so it is not like I am anti Keurig. I bought this machine for a convenience location, and it is anything but. I would not recommend this machine.'),
(2108, 10, 1, 4, '2015-10-06', 'Works great I\'ve had this little blender for close to a month, and it is definitely worth it considering the low price point. I would rate it 5 if not for the fact that you sometimes end up with bits of the food you are trying to blend leftover.  I made a banana/avocado smoothie this week and there were still little pieces of avocado left even after blending for a decent amount of time. That\'s not the type of food I would consider hard to blend smoothly. Haven\'t experienced any issues with the motor yet so I have nothing to complain about there.'),
(2109, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-28', 'Great product for great price Great price for a great product. It is individual size blender, it is fast to clean and very easy to use. I don\'t have any lumps in my smoothies, it does the job and very conveniently fits in a small kitchen. I would recommend it'),
(2110, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-29', 'Great toaster oven Works great for toast, reheating and baking. Good Value!'),
(2111, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-19', 'LOVING IT. easy to use, beautiful and versatile. who could want more from a coffeemaker. i had a bad experience with a hameltonbeach blender years ago. but this VERY different. their products must be first class now, because i\'m over the moon about this coffee pot!'),
(2112, 6, 1, 2, '2016-01-07', 'but ended up with the stainless cuisinart 4 slice toaster at Costco and it performs much better. We got two different ones, just in case the first was just a fluke. But unfortunately neither toasted well. Even at highest setting bread was barely toasted :( I really wanted a white one, but ended up with the stainless cuisinart 4 slice toaster at Costco and it performs much better.'),
(2113, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-16', 'This is a great coffee pot This is a great coffee pot.  I love the detachable water container and no annoying alarm at the end of the brew cycle - I can hear its done brewing which is all I need.  The adjustable heat for the warming tray and the adjustable brewing (mild or bold) are bonuses.  Only 2 ways to make this pot better: 1. add a k-cup option and 2. make the lid on the pot only attach to the handle rather than having a plastic ring around the top of the pot - mine doesn\'t drip yet but I can\'t imagine how eventually water won\'t get trapped in there from rinsing the pot and drip out when you fill your cup.  Get this pot - you won\'t be disappointed.'),
(2114, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-11', '... makes food that much more enjoyable to eat and best for lazy people like me blending things makes food that much more enjoyable to eat and best for lazy people like me'),
(2115, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'I ordered this for my neighbors and they absolutely love it. They said it was so much better ... I ordered this for my neighbors and they absolutely love it. They said it was so much better than their last name brand toaster. So worth the price.'),
(2116, 11, 1, 2, '2016-09-29', 'Toaster Oven Review after having for 2 years. I bought this toaster oven exactly 2 years ago and today it died. About 6 months ago the door broke and 2 weeks ago a piece of metal fell off the top into the toaster. I am replacing this with a different brand (Waring). Overall this toaster has been okay. It has toasted our bread and reheated pizza for us for 2 years. But, I am not replacing it with the same model. I\'d like to have one for about 5 years at least. Note: We use our toaster oven every single day, sometimes more than once a day so if you don\'t use it often, perhaps it would last longer.'),
(2117, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-27', 'So far great Great price and it works better than other toaster ovens I\'ve owned but had to pay allot more for. The digital feature is nice as opposed to having to turn one of those knobs like on some of them. It\'s very large I really like the capacity. I really have no complaints but if I do I guess I\'ll be back around to let y\'all know on a updated review. I\'ve had this for about a month so far.'),
(2118, 12, 1, 2, '2015-02-11', 'Clunky operation Very elegant look in kitchen. I would not order again nor recommend. Operation is clunky and bread slice does not get inside toast area. Sometimes it folds bread double and is hard to get out of toaster. A better idea with poor execution.'),
(2119, 7, 3, 4, '2014-12-12', 'For a small cup of coffee this brewer works fine.'),
(2120, 1, 1, 4, '2016-08-28', 'Like the slimmer size of this one compared to a ... Like the slimmer size of this one compared to a full size unit. Makes great coffee. The only reason I didn\'t give it 5 stars is that there is no auto shut off as we had with previous keurig machines.'),
(2121, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-29', 'Have had this coffee maker for 1 month and it ... Have had this coffee maker for 1 month and it is working well. The one draw back so far is having it set under the wall cabinet you have to pull it away from the wall each time in order to pull the coffee filter out and clean the coffee out. Otherwise seems to be working as it should.'),
(2122, 12, 1, 4, '2014-12-16', 'Four Stars its not as big as i thought it would be however its small enough to store.'),
(2123, 2, 1, 4, '2016-10-10', 'It does the job I got rid of my ideal tosteroven for the reason I purchased this one. Weight. I had a GE that was everything one could ask for but I\'m  an older single woman and felt it was dangerous for me be carrying it in and out of the garage (it did not fit in my cabinets). This Black and Decker does the job but on a much smaller scale. It\'s easy to use, easy to store. It fits in my cabinet and a large baked potato fit inside. I\'d like it to be a bit larger....'),
(2124, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-19', 'Good cheap coffee maker! I like that it is very easy to program, fill and use.  It does not take up much space on the counter, which is also nice.  The thing I do not much like is that the water does not seem to get hot enough to properly brew the coffee, so the coffee just does not taste like it should.'),
(2125, 5, 1, 1, '2015-10-06', 'Bought this coffee maker over a month ago. Glass ... Bought this coffee maker over a month ago.  Glass on the carafe is so thin, that it cracked and therefore the essential part of the COFFEE maker is gone.  Over the past month, there is no carafe in stock on Hamiltonbeach.com NOR is it expected anytime soon, with reps promising dates of arrival here and there that is never true.  Would not want to purchase a product that does not have spare parts to it.  Especially parts that essentially make the ENTIRE product..  Never buying Hamilton Beach and would suggest so to anyone thinking about it.'),
(2126, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-12', 'Five Stars Love it. Spacious'),
(2127, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-21', 'One Star It came broken.'),
(2128, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Wonderful! Best price we found anywhere for this well made coffee maker.  The on-demand feature is outstanding.  It brews the best coffee of any coffee maker we\'ve ever had, probably due to the charcoal watefr filter.  An outstanding product from an outstanding manufacturer.'),
(2129, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-10', 'Great small machine This machine is great which makes good tasting coffee and tea. It is so convenient in the kitchen as the size is small. I simply like this machine'),
(2130, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Super easy Love the convenience, reliability and taste of the coffee the K250 makes. I buy the costco breakfast blend 200 package and it is very economical. Never looked back, would recommend to anyone looking for a low maintenance coffee maker. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2131, 8, 1, 1, '2016-10-27', 'Love Love it! Perfect size for 1-2 people.'),
(2132, 6, 1, 4, '2016-12-03', 'Four Stars Good value.'),
(2133, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-03', 'easy to small, powerful, easy to use'),
(2134, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-14', 'Five Stars love it my diet starts now'),
(2135, 10, 1, 3, '2015-10-14', 'Not as good as the last one bought You get what you pay for. Not as good as the last one bought...'),
(2136, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-05', 'Compact and Portable Good...cute n does it job well.'),
(2137, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-21', 'Great Coffee Maker Our 2nd Cuisinart coffee maker quit working and I researched Amazon reviews for the best option for the price and I think I found it. Brew Options (regular, 1-4 cups, or bold). Convenient removal of the coffee grinds filter.  Just press the button on the side and the front panel opens up for easy access to the coffee filter.  Easy fill container.  No more having to fill the coffee craft with water.  Just rotate the coffee maker 180 degrees (on rollers) to remove the water container from the back, remove and fill at the sink then replace. Set up the night before and program the time you want it to start.  The coffee maker turns off automatically at 2 hours only, however if you want to keep it hot longer, you can either turn it back on for another 2 hours or select the \"keep warm\" button and select the temperature of the hot plate you prefer. After nearly 2 weeks, we are very please with this product.'),
(2138, 7, 3, 5, '2016-07-02', 'I broke the carafe for our old coffee maker. Butter fingers (me) dropped it in the sink. Decided to find a single serve coffee maker. If you love scalding hot coffee that also tastes good then this is your coffee maker. You can make it really strong or regular. Clean up is easy. no more large glass carafe to fumble around with. It\'s easy to lift the lid to get access to the water reservoir. place your coffee packet in the holder press down and hit the brew button. Shoot you can do it in your sleep. It also has the capability to use coffee grounds also. Hamilton Beach finally made a great product. Love, love,love it. If it breaks that\'s okay. I\'ll run to Walmart and get another . No questions or reservations about this coffee maker. The price is just right. Inexpensive!!! you will not regret purchasing this coffee maker. Can\'t say enough good things about it. Love good tasting coffee!'),
(2139, 11, 1, 2, '2014-08-15', 'Does the job? Works fine for roasting veggies but I didn\'t notice that one of the bottom rubber pieces that the toaster rests on was missing, until after I used it.  So now I have a wobbly toaster.'),
(2140, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'Five Stars Gut'),
(2141, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-13', 'Works so far perfect. I only needed it for hot chocolate for my husband. I use the little pods. Comes out in as little one and half minutes.'),
(2142, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'Five Stars Just right for 2 big mugs.'),
(2143, 10, 1, 3, '2015-05-06', 'Can\'t complain at under $20 Works fine, feels chintzy as one might have expected for an under $20 blender.  Have to be careful not to overload.'),
(2144, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-22', 'Four Stars WAS MISSING TRAYS'),
(2145, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-12', 'Five Stars Perfect for a small family. I am happy with this product.'),
(2146, 8, 1, 4, '2016-04-27', 'Perfect size but had an issue with the handle loosening ... Perfect size but had an issue with the handle loosening from the carafe after only a few uses.  Needed to have original purchase replaced.'),
(2147, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-27', 'good toaster for price. We\'ve been using this toaster for three months now, so I think that is long enough for a fair review. I\'ve found it to toast evenly, both sides,  and the different settings do make a difference (bagel, warm, etc.) I would gladly purchase again.'),
(2148, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-16', 'Keurig Brewing is Great This is my 3rd Keurig machine.  My 1st lasted almost 6 years and 2nd only 14 months.  The K250 is a nice machine but the water it holds is smaller than others.  It is a very quiet machine and the coffee comes out great as with other machines.  I haven\'t tried the carafe option yet.  Thanks Keurig for free pods for providing unbiased review.'),
(2149, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Best Decision I made about Coffee this year. I love everything about this coffeemaker!  When I read that it was in the top 5 of best coffeemakers, I decided to try it. It has lived up to all of the reviews.  The coffee is great,filling it is easy, and I can\'t think of anything I would add- unless it would be someone to bring it to my bedroom in the morning.'),
(2150, 3, 1, 4, '2014-12-15', 'Four Stars Great toaster oven. My only complaint is that the surface gets too hot when using.'),
(2151, 6, 1, 1, '2015-07-17', 'Looks nice but does not toast evenly Looks nice but does not toast evenly. I t has not worked since the day we purchased it. I would return it but it is past its return date due. Our old cheap toaster worked better than this piece of junk. Part of the toast comes out completely un toasted and part of it burns. Don\'t waist your money. Unfortunately cuisinart is not what it used to be.'),
(2152, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-12', 'Five Stars great maker, good price'),
(2153, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'good product good price use it a lot and it does a great job for all the things you will want!  pretty straightforward.  good product.  good price.'),
(2154, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Works great. No complaints Works great. No complaints. This is my first coffee machine so I have nothing to compare it to but it beats instant coffee. Has a nice clock. Decent size glass pitcher. Makes it fast and thourough. Hope this will last me many years'),
(2155, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-04', 'Love the look and features Had this toaster for 3 years. Still works great. Still looks great. Love the warm up feature and everything else. As far as toasters go I dont see them getting any better than this.'),
(2156, 9, 1, 1, '2015-12-18', 'After one month, the reservoir began leaking uncontrollably. This coffee maker makes an excellent cup of coffee and the reservoir does an excellent job keeping all of the coffee hot, but still fresh-tasting, for four hours. HOWEVER, after only one month of use, the reservoir started leaking uncontrollably one day, rendering the coffee maker unusable.  Basically, the coffee went straight through the machine and out the spout, leaking all over the counter top.  Even if you catch the coffee in a cup as it comes out, the coffee is not hot, since it does not stay in the machine.  We called Cuisinart and were told during a forty-five second conversation that there was no fix and we could either return it to the store or ship it back to them, at our cost.  This was our second try, since the first machine was broken in the box.  Needless to say, it is going back to the store and I will try a new brand. It is too bad, because I really wanted this to work.'),
(2157, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-07', 'Great coffee maker! Coffee maker is great! Love having the separate  container in back for the water & coffee pot doesn\'t drip when pouring. Don\'t understand any of the concerns others have written about. Set up the coffee maker in 2 minutes & was ready to use.'),
(2158, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-25', 'Five Stars Love this Kuerig, coffee is hot and rich tasting.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(2159, 12, 1, 5, '2015-10-18', 'Works! Oven small I got this to toast bagels and to heat frozen things for my kids. It is perfect for that purposes.  It is small which I like- less space taken up on kitchen counter. Oven rack and tray is very small- fits two patties side by side. This is fine for me because I\'m heating small amount of food to feed two littlish kids- mainly for lunches. For meals for four, I\'m definitely using regular oven. This oven heats up fast and is powerful (?) - burned food quickly when I set it to 400 as frozen food box instructed. Since then, I\'m baking everything at 350 and monitor. It\'s super simple to use, it does bake food to oven baked crispness so I\'m really happy with it.'),
(2160, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'A great smoothie maker. It is nice for single person use to make smoothies.'),
(2161, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-13', 'I\'d buy another one, and if they have this model in about a year, I will do just that! As expected.  I AM surprised at how much cheap toaster ovens cost these days, but you are totally safe ordering this one or any version very similar.  This has more heating options on it than I need.  Looks very sleek.  I like it.'),
(2162, 11, 1, 4, '2015-12-18', 'Great toaster - though beware of always on MODE - could be very dangerous Really great, though one small thing,  it\'s possible to leave this product on indefinitely, if you turn the timer dial counter clockwise too far, which I think is a very bad design decision.  It only happened to me once, and then I realized that would happen.  But, I could see a lot of people accidentally turning it on in that mode on accident - which doesn\'t seem safe.'),
(2163, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-09', 'Five Stars love it'),
(2164, 7, 3, 3, '2016-09-30', 'I use a bit larger cup and find the coffee weak. Wouldn\'t think of using a travel mug with this brewer'),
(2165, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-19', 'Excellent Coffee Maker! This is one awesome coffee maker!  We used to have a Cuisinart coffee maker that was an automatic grind and brew machine, but had to retire it.  For the price, this coffee maker is excellent!  Even though it doesn\'t grind fresh beans, it makes a really good cup or cups of coffee.  I like the water tank is removable, the timer works, and the buttons/functions are simple and straightforward.'),
(2166, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-29', 'Five Stars Good one.'),
(2167, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'It\'s easy to use and quite roomy We were looking for just a regular toaster oven to replace our old one  and this one fit the bill.  It\'s easy to use and quite roomy, seems easy to clean.  .  We have made toast, bagels, chicken and country ribs so far in it and it works great.  We are quite pleased  with this product.'),
(2168, 7, 3, 4, '2015-01-02', 'Bought this coffee maker for second home - a studio apt. I readreviewsreviewsreviews and had a little concern but cost was too good. Bought on Walmart site. Saved $10. Need to get comfortable with snapping in kcup and sliding it in. Has to be just right. When done correctly its fine. Without kcup my son overflowed over the counter but I believe that was human error and not the machine. Just bought it for Christmas. So far happy with my purchase'),
(2169, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-29', 'Great coffee maker! This a great coffee maker that pours one cup at a time.  I really like this one over the more traditional models.'),
(2170, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-12', 'Great Toaster with Lots of Options Love this toaster, has all the right settings and can take 4 pieces of bread at the same time, even has a defrost button.'),
(2171, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-08', 'Love everything about it Many many functions. Love everything about it.'),
(2172, 9, 1, 4, '2016-03-23', 'We love the \"on demand\" feature This is my 4th coffee on demand coffee maker.  We love the \"on demand\" feature, but the water reservoir on the newer model is very difficult to clean with small spaces, ledges, and spikes (to hold the filter) at the bottom.  Poor design, plus, the filter does not rest on the drain area and, therefore,  seems useless. BUT, we still love it!'),
(2173, 7, 3, 5, '2016-12-26', 'We love it because you can use regular coffee grounds or the pods.'),
(2174, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-29', 'Cute little blender I like this little machine. It\'s perfect for making single serving smoothies. My only tip is to cut up everything before putting it in the blender. I made the mistake of putting a frozen banana in without chopping it and I struggled a little bit. I would recommend adding your liquid and protein powder, blending, and then adding chopped frozen bananas or whatever you\'re going to add. You also have to hold the button down, which I didn\'t know when buying it, but it\'s not a big deal.'),
(2175, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-28', 'The product is pretty good but just has a little bit smell The product is pretty good but just has a little bit smell! I have been using for a week to make my smoothy'),
(2176, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-23', 'Four Stars Good for drinks and smooth.'),
(2177, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-31', 'A good machine for the $ A quality, easy-to-program and easy-to-clean coffee maker. The only negative is that the front top plate tends to pop off, but I am otherwise so pleased with it that I\'ve still given it five stars.'),
(2178, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-24', 'It works best if you pulse It has a little bit of trouble working through some frozen berries and takes way longer than a normal blender, but I wanted something small and portable, and it does the job (eventually.) I have to stir it to coax it along sometimes. It works best if you pulse, pause, stir and repeat.'),
(2179, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-30', 'My first Keurig and I love it! The Keurig K250 2.0 Brewer has the feature I\'ve been waiting for...the ability to brew a larger cup of coffee. I am able to brew a 14 ounce cup using a K-MUG pod or a 30 ounce carafe using a K-CARAFE pod. The coffee flavor and temperature are consistent every time. It would be nice to have more flavor choices with the larger brewing options. The only negative is that the brewer consistently dispenses one ounce less than the amount chosen on the touch screen. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2180, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-29', '2.0 Keurig We have had our 2.0 for about a week now and are very happy with it.  I love the option to brew a carafe, and I like that it filters the water.  However, there are a few brands of pods that do not work with the new model that I will miss.  Also, I wish it had a timed auto off feature like my earlier version.  Otherwise, we are quite happy!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2181, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'it\'s all the things I have been expecting out of a microwave Stainless steel and Black & Decker. What you\'d get when you combine both things is a microwave that does more than just heat your food.'),
(2182, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Five Stars Perfect!!!'),
(2183, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Five Stars Quality item, I use mine everyday.'),
(2184, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'can keep food warm Its good, it can keep the bread warm for a long time'),
(2185, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-25', 'Great Toaster Oven! Bought this for my mom for Christmas as a replacement from her old one and she loves it.  Her stove does not work, so you can imagine that she used this for all of her cooking.  She does all of her baking of pizzas, meat, i.e.  It works great and the heat is evenly distributed.  One thing I noticed when I do use it though is that it bakes best with the rack on the lowest setting for bread because the top can burn easily.'),
(2186, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Five Stars Love this toaster.  Perfect toast and great toto aster oven.  Works well'),
(2187, 9, 1, 3, '2015-01-16', 'Three Stars First day to use it.  Will let you know as time goes by.'),
(2188, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-04', 'Buy this Toaster! LOVE this toaster! Great quality and super space saving! It will allow you to either use the toaster oven feature inside for frozen pizzas or warming up food, etc. or toast up to 4 pieces of bread at once (2 on top and 2 on the tray inside). Super easy to clean - much better than a traditional toaster because you can clean the inside well. Happy Customer!'),
(2189, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Four Stars Easy to use and you can have a great tasting coffee right on your fingertips. This is our first Keurig and an anniversary gift from my husband_ I\'m a coffee lover and this gift will be treasured.'),
(2190, 8, 1, 3, '2016-09-16', 'Three Stars Size is good.'),
(2191, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-17', 'Great Little toaster. Great little toaster. Very happy with it\'s size and functions flawlessly. Love it.'),
(2192, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Five Stars everything perfect'),
(2193, 11, 1, 3, '2015-07-09', 'does the job, however we\'ve burnt lots of toast ... does the job, however we\'ve burnt lots of toast as you have to set the toaster each time you turn it on, rather than being able to set the toaster to the desired degree of toasting and having it stay set.'),
(2194, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-04', 'This is a great little toaster This is a great little toaster.  Had one just like it for years and wore it out.  Now I can see how long the new models last. Sister Jay.'),
(2195, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'In love with my Keurig!! I am absolutely in LOVE with this system! I have never been much of a coffee drinker and couldn\'t justify buying it, until I had coffee with my neighbor and she used her Keurig. I ran right out and bought one. I wanted orange since it would match my kitchen, but Kohls doesnt carry it in stock here, so I grabbed black since I didnt want to wait. I am now an addicted coffee drinker and so are my late teens boys and husband. We enjoy coffee together every morning and some evenings. Wish I would have bought it sooner!! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2196, 11, 1, 4, '2015-02-03', 'Four Stars Good, but one time it turned on by itself. I had to unplug it.'),
(2197, 2, 1, 3, '2016-10-22', 'Three Stars Slow toast.'),
(2198, 11, 1, 5, '2015-04-04', 'Alittle small for me BUT i love it. Im not good with sizes. So its small for me, i will have to make like a mini flat meatloaf. But it has been good for me so far. And I MUST SAY THE FASTEST SHIPPING IN MY HISTORY WITH AMAZON. THANK YOU. I ordered another and when it was done a $44. Item ended up being $60. I could not afford it. Free ship but only with Prime so i cancelled it. It was a larger one. So all and all it works for me. The food would just be for me. Its nice looking and suits me for now. When you live on a budget you make choices. Im happy with it and say buy it. Thanks again for the quick service. Thx Peace'),
(2199, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-06', 'Great purchase Great purchase.'),
(2200, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-07', 'a multifunctional toaster - not just for bread anymore I moved into a new house just weeks before I finally got this toaster. This house is my first \"owned\" house and, bit by bit, I\'m ordering what I need to turn house into a home. This toaster is a wonderful addition to my kitchen. It has lots of settings, not just for bread, but bagel, defrost, and reheat, too. I love my sandwiches and my jelly a lot better on toast than on plain bread. And it\'s wonderful at toasting English muffins, though next time, I need to get the type that is fork-split rather than pre-sliced. My not-butter and honey tastes great on the toasted muffin. This does a wonderful job for me, and I\'m sure you\'ll love it, too. I\'d give it ten stars if I could.'),
(2201, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-29', 'Cool stuff Bought for my friend. She loves it. Now another friend wants.'),
(2202, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-14', 'I love this coffee maker I love this coffee maker!  I like how it shows how much coffee is left in the reservoir; I like how the water container lifts off, so there\'s no pouring into the reservoir; and, most of all, I love that it does not leak onto my white counter top!  It\'s well made and makes great coffee--so worth the extra money I paid over the Mr. Coffee one that I replaced after a part broke off!.'),
(2203, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'I wanted something compact for work and I love it! Works great Was skeptical about this little blender as I have a huge Vitamix and wasn\'t sure what to expect.  I wanted something compact for work and I love it! Works great.  I just usually let frozen fruit defrost a bit before I use it and also only blend for about 20 - 30 seconds at a time to make sure I dont overheat the motor.  Loving it!  Some of my co-workers have been borrowed it LOL'),
(2204, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-18', 'so good. This is used every day So far, so good.  This is used every day, multiple times a day and it\'s been great.  I love the pull-out reservoir in the back rather than just having to fill canister and pour into the machine. I\'ve been very pleased with Hamilton Beach products that we have, and this one is no different.'),
(2205, 2, 1, 1, '2015-11-11', 'Horrible product shape Item arrived with huge dents, it couldn\'t even stand straight.'),
(2206, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-11', 'Perfect for the Coffee Addict in your life We love our Keurig 2.0 K200! Usually we would brew a whole pot and throw away at least half. I really like being able to switch up what I\'m going to drink. I can drink a cup of tea, and then a cup of coffee without wasting the whole pot. The carafe is a great idea for when company is over and for holidays. Although I was a little disappointed because I thought the 2.0 came with the carafe. Apparently it\'s sold separately. Overall we love it! It does make a clicking sound when the water is pulled into the machine to heat up, but it\'s not overly loud. The drink is SUPER HOT when it comes out. Hotter than our other Keurig.'),
(2207, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-10', 'Five Stars Works great!'),
(2208, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-14', 'Five Stars Only had toaster for a few weeks. Works perfectly.'),
(2209, 6, 1, 5, '2016-10-30', 'Very good toaster Finally tossed an old Oster toaster and purchased this Cuisinart.  After playing around with the temps for toast, bagels, toaster pastries and frozen waffles, I think I\'ve finally the most pleasing settings for me.  This weekend I discovered that with the dial on 3, Toaster Strudels and frozen waffles come out perfectly if I use the Defrost button.  I wish I had room on my counter top for the 4-slice model, because so far, I\'m pleased with the 2-slice model.'),
(2210, 4, 1, 2, '2015-10-03', 'Cracked Heating Element Liked it a lot while it worked. Only three years after we bought it, though (and of course now it\'s no longer under their $30 \"warranty\"), one of the heating elements is cracked, as has happened to so many others in these reviews. I wish I had read more reviews before buying it, and I obviously cannot recommend this toaster. If only there was an affordable toaster out there that didn\'t have reviews talking about what junk it is...'),
(2211, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-03', 'received received.'),
(2212, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-17', 'Nice toaster Black + Decker has always been a good brand and this toaster is a good value.'),
(2213, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-12', 'Five Stars best coffee maker I had love great buy east to  use an  cl.ean'),
(2214, 2, 1, 1, '2016-05-15', 'I HAVE A VERY SMALL KITCHEN AND IT IS PERFECT FOR WHAT I WANT I HAVE USED THIS TOASTER OVEN FOR YEARS.  I HAVE A VERY SMALL KITCHEN AND IT IS PERFECT FOR WHAT I WANT.  THIS IS THE FIRST TIME I HAVE GIVEN THIS RATING FOR THIS ITEM.  IT SEEMS I MUST HAVE RECEIVED A LEMON AS THE ONE AND ONLY SHELF IS RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE OF THE OVEN.  IF I WANT TO HEAT A MUFFIN I HAVE TO CUT IT IN HALF OR IT WILL HIT THE HEATING COIL. I HAVE HAD THREE ITEMS OF FOOD GO ON FIRE AND I\'VE ONLY HAD IT A COUPLE OF MONTHS.  I WOULD NOT RECOMMEND THIS AT ALL.'),
(2215, 7, 3, 5, '2014-01-02', 'Very good for the money and quality.'),
(2216, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-11', 'Very Safisfied Purchased as a Christmas gift for my father.  The unit came in a nice box and had easy to follow instructions on how to use the oven for various cooking operations.  It has the ability to toast,  bake,  and broil.  My favorite is making tostitos pizza rolls in it!  Very satisfied and the unit is working as intended.'),
(2217, 2, 1, 1, '2016-01-14', 'In flames Too hot, too fast. Created Electrical fire.'),
(2218, 7, 3, 5, '2016-03-25', 'I am totally impressed. For the money it is the best single serve coffee maker that use the coffee pods on the market. Has many more features I like than Keurig. You especially can use any brand of coffee pods as well as regular grounds without an adapter. Good job Hamilton Beach!'),
(2219, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-08', 'Five Stars Great product and price!.'),
(2220, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-04', 'Four Stars It was a gag gift'),
(2221, 2, 1, 4, '2016-10-16', 'Good machine with ONE flaw. I\'ve only had this toaster for a few days and so far it works great. Toasts and bakes just as you\'d want it to An unpleasant odor burned off after first use). But it has one annoying design flaw: The power cord is really short. So unless you want your toaster to sit DIRECTLY in front of the outlet you plug it into, you\'re going to have to get an extension cord. I did, and now it\'s fine, but for crying out loud!  The cord barely reaches beyond the width of the toaster.  Dumb.'),
(2222, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-25', 'So far, so...excellent I got this as a Christmas gift and have been using it constantly (five times a day) for a month now along with using it three times for guests when the daily usage went up to 15. It has worked flawlessly for coffee, tea, and hot chocolate. I love good coffee and while it might seem blasphemous to say this, I LIKE Keurig coffee. When I brewed my own coffee, the first cup or two were delicious but the rest of the pot always tasted stale even though I stored the coffee in a carafe and did not keep it over constant heat. With the Keurig, I get that \"first cup\" taste every time. I assumed I would use the Keurig only occasionally but now it\'s my main coffee machine. No plastic smell, which I\'m very sensitive to and formerly made my coffee in a way that touched paper, glass, and stainless steel--never any plastic. Now I\'m making coffee in an all-plastic machine but I\'m loving it. Regarding cleaning the machine and how it do on the test of time...I do not know because I\'ve had it only for a month. But I\'ve put 200 or more pods through it in that time and, as the man said while falling off a skyscraper...\"So far, so good.\"'),
(2223, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'Five Stars Love the stainless steel.  Makes the room look alive.'),
(2224, 1, 1, 1, '2016-08-27', 'Don\'t buy this I hate this machine.  It wont take many pods (Green Mountain, etc)  Sorry I bought it.'),
(2225, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-23', 'coffe maker was great idea. My husband has become a coffee-holic....coffe maker was great idea....the K-cups retail are expensive !.'),
(2226, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-02', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(2227, 10, 1, 3, '2015-03-18', 'Good for some things If you\'re looking to quickly mix up some protein powder with a liquid, this is for you. Don\'t expect to be able to blend many frozen fruits, ice, etc. It works for some things but just wasn\'t enough power for me. Ended up using for about a weak then shoving in the back of my cabinet. I would recommend forking out the extra for the nutribullet which can blend anything. I bought it a few weeks ago and love it.'),
(2228, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-13', 'Love this coffee maker Love this coffee maker.  This is the third on-demand coffee maker I have had, but this is the first Cuisinart and my favorite.  Love the water filter feature.  Water quality in our area is poor, and the filter improves the taste of the coffee.'),
(2229, 7, 3, 2, '2015-01-16', 'Seal didn\'t appear good enough between pot & k-cup, returning it.'),
(2230, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-23', '... to mix his protein in my drinks it was perfect. I learned to completely dissolve power in a ... Once I learned how to mix his protein in my drinks it was perfect. I learned to completely dissolve power in a little liquid of whatever I\'m making first, cold or hot, then add liquid a little at a time stirring as you add. No lumps and practically no change in texture. I taught my sister how to do it now all of my powder is gone...Got to get some more!'),
(2231, 7, 3, 3, '2016-06-03', 'This product worked well. Although when I bought it I did not know it didn\'t have a choice for your ounces. I\'m guessing you put in the amount of water you want for the amount of coffee u would like. I\'ve only used it once so I\'m not real familiar with it yet. But I think it will be ok especially for the price.'),
(2232, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-27', 'Five Stars It is very nice'),
(2233, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'Thumbs mostly up We were so excited when we got this and our first time to try to use we realized we had cups that weren\'t official k cups, so no using the new coffee maker. Lovely... We went to get k cups, of course. Once we got some (and found tutorials on tricking the machine) we had our first cups of coffee. 6 cups later we had issues again. It was sputtering, not making the size cup we\'d chosen, etc. We cleaned the pod holder and did a cleansing brew (twice). We didn\'t descale because we weren\'t too annoyed to buy something to make our brand new coffee maker work! It is now working wonderfully. Right size, flowing correctly and not too hard to resolve. I still don\'t like that keurig is greedy by making the machine use keurig branded cups ONLY, but we do like the coffee maker. Full disclosure for why I wrote the review. (It definitely didn\'t change my opinion/bias my review)-Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2234, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-18', 'Great for kitchen counter This toaster is great for my kitchen counter. I can\'t think of anything I can\'t reheat in here. This is especially good for me as I am always busy and don\'t have a microwave.'),
(2235, 4, 1, 1, '2015-07-18', 'Dangerous!  FIRE HAZARD: Do not buy The metal on the heating coil cracked and the exposed area is glowing bright orange.  This is a fire hazard. This product should be recalled.'),
(2236, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-09', 'Five Stars makes my coffee just right.'),
(2237, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-03', 'Five Stars I\'m really happy with this . . . the \"reheat\" option is brilliant!'),
(2238, 7, 3, 5, '2016-11-24', 'I can use either K cups or regular coffee by using an insert included with the machine. This would make a great gift for the coffee lover on your Christmas of Hannakuh list'),
(2239, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-28', 'Four Stars Makes great toast'),
(2240, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-28', 'Great Toaster Great little toaster.  All the settings you need to make great toast for a reasonable price.  Looks great, easy to store, nice quality, pretty white plastic.  Two features I like are the warming setting (already toasted but bread needs warmed) and the lever to raise the toast so you can easily grab it without the need to put a fork or knife to spear the bread.'),
(2241, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-30', 'Really like this, Black & Decker is always a reliable ... Really like this, Black & Decker is always a reliable choice. The knobs seem a bit stiff and harder to turn than previous models I\'ve owned. Compact, fits nicely on my counter without taking up too much space, and cooks very well.'),
(2242, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-14', 'Great coffee maker and a bargain Love this coffee pot. Easy to fill. Easy to clean. Makes good coffee. Yay for bargains!'),
(2243, 4, 1, 4, '2015-07-28', 'Four Stars Door tends to open slightly went heating up'),
(2244, 11, 1, 1, '2014-07-28', 'Doesn\'t get hot enough to make toast Toaster gets warm, but not hot enough to toast.  Definitely does not get up to the temperature set for baking.'),
(2245, 10, 1, 1, '2015-04-05', 'One Star this broke after my 6 use and it is cheaply made! I would never purchase again'),
(2246, 9, 1, 1, '2015-09-15', 'Lever gets stuck The lever gets stuck and won\'t stop pouring out coffee.  This has happened three times and we\'ve had it a month.  We are going to try and return.'),
(2247, 4, 1, 4, '2015-10-02', 'This is quite Impressive toaster ovan. Highly sophisticated high tech! This is quite a bit more expensive than other brands but I can bake so much more with 2 racks. It fits a 12\" pizza. We use it almost every day. We don\'t use the regular oven any more.'),
(2248, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-24', 'Great Toaster Oven Great, easy to use, little toaster with oven. Handy for warming and even some cooking.'),
(2249, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'Excellent product! I love this toaster oven.  We have used it a lot and it is very reliable and easy to clean.'),
(2250, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-29', 'Great coffee maker! Best coffee maker for the money. I love it!.'),
(2251, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-19', 'Five Stars It\'s cheap and it makes coffee.'),
(2252, 11, 1, 2, '2014-11-16', 'Did not meet my expectations at all. Find it ... Did not meet my expectations at all.  Find it difficult to operate.  Cannot fit four slices of toast as advertised.  cannot understand directions.'),
(2253, 12, 1, 5, '2016-11-05', 'Awesome Gadget This seems to be working great so far! Nice little toaster and oven 2 in 1. I have own this for about a week now used it a few times and so far I love it I only wish the black one was on sale at the same time of the red one, but I guess I can\'t complain I got it for a good price and it\'s a nice little space saver!.'),
(2254, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-12', 'Who needs luminosity? Just try to figure out these controls! This is a solid basic toaster over, to replace an earlier, similar B&D model that lasted a full 15 years in an office, which is amazing. But I swear they had a committee with the specific role to make the controls hard to read and decipher. After a while you catch on but sheeeeseh, it\'s a toaster over, not an F-16! The controls should be simple.'),
(2255, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-14', 'love it simple, functional, attractive. replaced my 20 year old black and decker. having the timer is a great safety and convenience addition.'),
(2256, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Wake-up and smell the coffee My wife and I recently purchased a Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing system and we can\'t believe we went this long without one. The simplicity and ease of using it is remarkable. No more emptying coffee grounds and washing the carafe ever time we want a cup of coffee. The machine will preheat the water for the first cup, less than a minute, and we can go about making breakfast and then get an instant cup of coffee. The second cup is ready to go in seconds. Since we come from the generation of the great depression we don\'t find a few seconds wait or a few droops variance in a cup of coffee something to complain about like some of the reviews state. Even if Keurig did not compensate us for this review, We would write it any way because we appreciate the wonders of modern engineering and the Keurig K250 2.0 Coffee maker which frees us from the drudgery of making conventional coffee.'),
(2257, 7, 3, 3, '2015-05-26', 'I needed a single-serve coffee maker for work so I was very excited about receiving this product however after giving it a go, I wasn\'t too pleased. The machine worked great but the finished coffee had a plastic taste. I\'ve only used it once so far and will continue trying it... I\'m hoping that plastic taste eventually goes away but I don\'t remember ever having this issue with my Keurig. A few pros are that it\'s easy, lightweight, and convenient. It has two heights for regular coffee cups and a taller travel mug. The product offers you two way to brew coffee including using a ready-to-go K-cup or filling it yourself with freshly ground coffee (which is the way I prefer it) I read other reviews about people having an issue with coffee spills and leaks so I\'m hoping I don\'t have those issues as well. If I\'m able to get that plastic taste away and don\'t have leak issues, this product will be perfect!'),
(2258, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-29', 'Replacement Keurig for an older model There are advantages and disadvantages to this model., which replaces the older model I owned. Disadvantages: There are some pods marked for Keurig brewers that I have left that the new model refuses to use.  The brewing itself is very slow by comparison with the old. Advantages: The carafe option is convenient. The water filtration system is nice to have. The options for size of cup are clearer. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2259, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-28', 'Three Stars It works okay. Cannot go wrong with this model and the price.'),
(2260, 4, 1, 5, '2017-01-13', 'Very Pleased - Right Size - Variety of Straightforward Functions - Easy to Clean!! Very pleased with this toaster oven. The controls are very straightforward, but this does not serve to diminish the overall quality of the device, nor does it make the device under-featured.  Just easy to use.  Cleaning, oh my gosh - the base pan is non-stick, flat with no sides and slides out for EASY rinse and wash in the sink - like about 90 seconds to clean a toaster oven!  Wow. The heating pattern on toast is uniform over the whole piece of bread and the ability to heat up food on a plate is quick and painless - with 7 different ways to heat up an item. Very attractive on the counter top and not overly large.  Definitely not the trashy looking thing one had in college.... Best toaster oven I have ever owned.'),
(2261, 3, 1, 2, '2015-01-12', 'Don\'t buy and expect to not get burned. Works well...I think I have burned myself 3 times.  This is NOT user or kid friendly.  All of the outside parts get screaming HOT!'),
(2262, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'Keurig 2.0 brewing system I am enjoying my Keurig2.0 brewing system, Orange. The coffee tastes so much better with the feature of controlling the strength. The color looks quite striking on my countertop.'),
(2263, 10, 1, 2, '2015-01-24', 'Two Stars IT BROKE AFTER A MONTH'),
(2264, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-01', 'Five Stars Perfect for making single serving smoothies. It blends well too.'),
(2265, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-20', 'Five Stars I love it!!.'),
(2266, 11, 1, 2, '2014-10-27', 'The inside tray is extremely hard to clean and has ... The inside tray is extremely hard to clean and has been stained black due to oil dripping onto it. It\'s impossible to get off, must be something with the coating on the tray.'),
(2267, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'You\'ll Wonder Why You Didn\'t Get One Sooner! A little piece of morning heaven!!!  I absolutely love my new Keurig 2.0 K200 Brewer. I\'ve had it now for a week and I\'ve used it every day. I mainly got it because I am the only one who drinks coffee in my household and was tired of throwing out coffee from the 12 cup regular brewer I had. Since getting this machine I\'ve actually cut my coffee consumption. It is also a lot faster to brew a single cup than half a pot. I hesitated purchasing one because of the non-reusable pods, reviews of other models, etc. However, when I researched the newer models (i.e. K200) it got so many great reviews I decided to give it a shot and I couldn\'t be happier. Yes, the pods are expensive but if you purchase the PureJava reusable pod refill and use your own coffee you\'ll wonder why you didn\'t purchase one sooner. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this honest review!'),
(2268, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-19', 'Four Stars Convenient to use'),
(2269, 6, 1, 3, '2015-08-18', 'Good for the money I have only used the toast function so far, but it works very well. Toast is done the way each person wants.'),
(2270, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Five Stars I love this blender! It is the perfect size for one person!'),
(2271, 4, 1, 4, '2016-01-30', 'Replacement needed, first lasted only 4 years. I really like the Cuisinart TOB-40 Custom Classic Toaster Oven Broiler, but after 4 years I just had to replace this Toaster, Oven and Broiler because the front bottom heating element  became distorted and warped, along with having a crack in the element.  I felt it could become a fire hazard.  Yet the other three heating elements are still in perfect condition. The front bottom heating element seemed became warped to the point that I had a very difficult time pulling out the crumb tray and also putting it back into the oven.  But I wanted to take pictures of the element so the Vendor could see the problem. The previous toaster oven lasted over ten years, so I was disappointed that the Cuisinart TOB-40 Custom Classic Toaster Oven Broiler only lasted for four years.  I just expected purchasing an name brand such as Cuisinart that their product would hold up to its name. Of course 4 years ago, they did not provide any Appliance Protection Plan.  Therefore the warranty had run out.  Hopefully, this replacement  will not be a lemon and will provide longevity since we only used it for toasting bread.'),
(2272, 12, 1, 1, '2014-06-12', 'Great idea but does not work Thought I could save some counter space but unit did not work out of the box.  The oven never came on.  Waste of my time.  Let me experience save you some time.'),
(2273, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker; keeps the coffee hot'),
(2274, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-10', 'am sure glad i order it best decision i made easy to ... am sure glad i order it best decision i made easy to clean works great its every thing i expected very happy'),
(2275, 7, 3, 5, '2016-12-04', 'I just open it up ,made some coffee it taste fine ,I wasn\'t looking for a real high price coffee m.its buit strong and looks cool .for thid price yes it work'),
(2276, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Five Stars Love it.'),
(2277, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Loving This Brewer Loving my Keurig 2.0 K250 brewer. I\'ve had coffee from the original Keurig before and I swear the coffee from this new brewer tastes better. My one complaint is the whole \"DRM\" system where you need an authorized K-cup. Of course there are ways around it.'),
(2278, 4, 1, 2, '2015-02-07', 'Two Stars Returned because there was no heat resentence  on the sides:>('),
(2279, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-18', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(2280, 5, 1, 3, '2016-10-11', 'I otherwise LOVE this coffee maker for the price Weak plastic, the faceplate over all the buttons broke off completely within a week of normal use. Unfortunate because, I otherwise LOVE this coffee maker for the price.'),
(2281, 9, 1, 3, '2015-05-24', 'Useless Filters After looking at the water filter and the reservoir, it is obvious the filter is useless. The way the filter fits into the bottom of the reservoir  allows water to flow underneath the filter. Water will take the path of least restriction. When I asked Cuisinart about this they said it was designed to operate with or without a filter. Save your money and don\'t use the filters, unless you seal the passages under the filter holder.  But then you will probably burn up the unit because of lack of water flow.'),
(2282, 11, 1, 4, '2014-03-18', 'Does the job This was my first toaster oven.  I don\'t use the bake option very often but I use the toast option to heat up almost everything, french toast sticks, waffles, tater tots, chicken nuggets, jimmy dean breakfast sandwiches, personal pan pizzas etc.  The top does get hot so you cant put anything on top of it. This is a much better option than turning on your oven or microwaving small food items. Using the microwave can make some food kinda rubbery and turning on the oven which makes your house hot for 1 corn dog is kinda silly. Great if you have small kids and you need to heat up meals for them.'),
(2283, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-08', 'Nice toaster, and a space saver It\'s a toaster, and it makes toast (and bagels, English muffins, etc.) very well.  I\'ve had the larger version of this toaster and was happy to find this compact model when I moved to a kitchen with limited counter space.  The slots are the same size as the big toaster, only the body is narrower.  Stays cool, does its job, I\'m happy.'),
(2284, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'Love it. Good looking too Love it.  Good looking too.'),
(2285, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-17', 'It`s everything I expected from Black & Decker, and ... It`s everything I expected from Black & Decker, and more.  I use it every day from breakfast toast to baking dinner meals.'),
(2286, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-26', 'LOVE IT!!!! I\'m so glad I got this despite a lot of the negative reviews. I love my little Keurig. I loved it so much that I bought another one for $20 from someone who never used hers. Yep, I\'m Keurig crazy now. Not to mention that I\'ve got my son AND hubby hooked. I was afraid that other brand K cups wouldn\'t work in this, but they do. I actually found some at the Dollar Tree- 4 for a dollar.... and it\'s delicious. I don\'t know about those of you who are coffee snobs, but you might want to give those a try before making judgement. Anyway, I am in LOVE with this thing. I actually created an entire little coffee bar for it. So some of you say that it doesn\'t make enough coffee for a larger cup, and I haven\'t taken the time to try the hacks that are out there to unlock the larger options, but I don\'t really need to. So here\'s what you do... if you have a 16 ounce cup, opt for the 10 ounce and let it fill. Then, lift the thingy and put it down again. Next, choose the 6 ounce option using the same k cup. If you absolutely HAVE to have SUPER strong coffee, then you might want to use a second k cup, but I wouldn\'t because it\'s still strong after the second brew. If you use \"Donut Shop\" coffee, it\'s strong even after the second brew. If you drink a ton of coffee and like the dollar store k cups, I\'d order them from the Dollar Tree dot com web site and have them shipped to the store without paying for shipping. Imagine, 25 cents a cup? Or even 50 cents. That\'s a heck of a deal. In any case.. as I always say, I haven\'t had any problems with my Keurig so I\'d highly recommend it to anyone. So there you have it. I love my Keurig!.'),
(2287, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-26', 'Five Stars Good for the price'),
(2288, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-29', 'Died fast I liked this coffee pot a lot but after 2 months it quit working. The lights on the display don\'t come on and there is no power to the machine. Hamilton Beach is replacing it but it\'s costing me 12.99 for shipping. I think if I got a bad machine I shouldn\'t have to pay another 12.99 for it. This will be my last Hamilton Beach for sure.'),
(2289, 4, 1, 1, '2015-01-30', 'Very disappointed. We have had this oven a little over a year and as it is burning the toast even on the lowest setting. Now I found that the bottom elements are busted open and although we haven\'t had a fire yet, it is very likely. This is unacceptable for the price. Very disappointed.'),
(2290, 2, 1, 1, '2016-01-31', 'Flimsy My old one had a tray in the bottom to pull out for cleaning, and a pan for cooking in.  This has just one flimsy \"drip tray/pan\".  Is just cheesy and I am going to have to buy a cooking tray.'),
(2291, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-14', 'It works great! Obsessed with this little blender.  I take it with me wherever I go so I can make my protein shakes. It works great!'),
(2292, 5, 1, 2, '2015-05-24', 'Good pot-until it dies worked  fine ... until just after the warranty was up! Used all the features, auto brew, auto shut off, different pot size settings, different strength settings-all well done! About 2 months after the warranty...kaput! I would not buy this unless you are willing to re-purchase it in about 380 days.'),
(2293, 11, 1, 1, '2014-05-11', 'Old merchandise I learned that this toaster oven was manufactured 1st quarter 2013.  I found screws had been stripped, not smooth on top--like this unit was reconditioned and not new as advertised.'),
(2294, 2, 1, 3, '2015-05-30', 'Three Stars This toaster oven is very small.  Unless you are cooking very small portions this machine is not handy.'),
(2295, 8, 1, 2, '2015-02-19', 'Two Stars Average'),
(2296, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-29', 'It\'s pretty good looking and does an awesome job The blender works well. It\'s pretty good looking and does an awesome job. The only thing I didn\'t like, was that you cannot take off the blades, so you must take them everywhere you go.'),
(2297, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-19', '2.5 years and still going strong I\'ve had this coffee maker for 2.5 years now and it\'s still going strong.  I use the program feature everyday and I\'ve never had any issues with it.  I typically brew it on the bold setting.  I love that brew basket swings out and has the button release.  My favorite feature is the removable water reservoir.  Makes it so easy to fill without having to pour water into a container and then pouring into the reservoir.  Oh and it does its main job pretty well too: tasty coffee!'),
(2298, 4, 1, 5, '2015-09-24', 'Five Stars I love it'),
(2299, 9, 1, 4, '2015-11-30', 'Very good product. The only issue is that the coffee ... Very good product.  The only issue is that the coffee basket is too small for the maximum capacity of 12 cups. The coffee basket holds the equivalent quantity of maximum 8 cups of coffee.'),
(2300, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-16', 'Five Stars Works like a champ! Love this blender!'),
(2301, 11, 1, 4, '2016-05-30', 'Four Stars Very nice for the money.'),
(2302, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-22', 'black and decker toaster oven TO1303SB 4 slice toaster oven this works well and looks very nice but I didn\'t like the dial to turn it to off position.  I thought I turned it off but it was confusing that I turned it to \"stay on\" position.'),
(2303, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-12', 'Best upgrade yet!!!!! This new version that Keurig has come up with has blown me away!!! I have used keurigs before at work but wouldn\'t make the plunge to buy my own because I had some concerns. After recieving this new version free for testing purposes I was so impressed that Keurig had answered all the lingering questions and concerns I previously had. Detailed instructions & accessories on how to clean you Keurig including the FILTER! Also the option for cup sizes & strength of the coffee & you can now make 4 cups at once!!! I was worried that the new features would be difficult for some people to get the hang of but everyone in my house has been using it with ease!!!!! Awesome upgrade Keurig!!!'),
(2304, 5, 1, 1, '2015-08-30', 'I liked it. It\'s sad that manufacturers no longer take ... I ordered this in January of 2015 and it now will not even turn on. This product didn\'t even last a year. What a shame because, otherwise, I liked it. It\'s sad that manufacturers no longer take pride in their product and simply want to turn out product that dies fast so we spend more money.'),
(2305, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-25', '... was a gift but I\'m sure it will be great!! It was a gift but I\'m sure it will be great!!'),
(2306, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-17', 'Five Stars Good price, perfect for small kitchen'),
(2307, 5, 1, 4, '2016-12-28', 'No broken faceplate yet, very good coffee and all the features work well so far! It was worth the risk. A few bad units? Our faceplate wasn\'t broken, and hasn\'t broken yet. I took it apart (annoying) to see if ours might break eventually, but it was fine inside. No cracks, or weirdness. I noticed the two pegs were slightly wider than the holes in the control board where they go, so I widened the holes and replaced the plate while being careful not to over tighten the screws. Looks good for now! Someone else said the carafe leaks all over or something. Well, our carafe pours very well with no drips, but I can see how if you tried to dump it all out at once the coffee might overflow the little dam near the spout and go everywhere. The plastic of the housing is rather soft and pliable, but seems to stay very clean from coffee. The top of the housing is a little warpy, and looks cheap. But, this seems to be a purely aesthetic problem. Since I opened mine to check out the faceplate issue, I can say that the interior seems well put together and didn\'t observe anything else that might become a problem. Also there is, of course, one abnormal screw in the bottom which prevents users from opening it with a normal philips. I had to make a screwdriver to get it out. The coffee is waaay better than our old mr coffee type brewer, and we like the adjustable temp warming pad. If you\'re cheap like me, then give it a try! You can always just glue the faceplate back on, since the two pegs where screws hold it on are the only thing that breaks, and the control board behind it is sealed up independently of the plate. I love it, but I\'m not giving it five stars because I\'m annoyed with HB for making me worry about the stupid faceplate.'),
(2308, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-20', 'Best coffee pot I\'ve ever had Best coffee pot I\'ve ever had; far superior to Mr. Coffee.  Easy to fill, excellent spout (no overflow when pouring).  I do wish it had a signal indicating when the coffee is done, but this is a small matter.'),
(2309, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-15', 'great useful appliance for the kitchen wonderfully priced quality performance'),
(2310, 5, 1, 5, '2014-05-26', 'Does the job well I can\'t improve upon the very thorough reviews that already sing the praises of this coffee maker. I can only add one feature that is a vast improvement over my previous Hamilton Beach coffee maker -- a pause & serve capability that does not drip! I had a Hamilton Beach designer brand whose name I can\'t remember now. It also was programmable, had a removable water reservoir, and a pause & serve capability -- my three main requirements. You can never tell whether that last feature really works until you actually use the machine. I\'m very pleased that the feature works well on this unit. My last coffee maker drove me nuts. Every time I removed the carafe to pour coffee while it was still brewing, water would drip all over the burner below because the stopper didn\'t properly close. It didn\'t take long before the non-stick coating was almost completely worn away and no matter how much I cleaned it, it looked unsightly. The first time I used this coffee maker I very slowly and carefully removed the carafe while the coffee was still brewing, fully expecting the dribble onto the burner from a poorly seated stopper -- but it never materialized! No drip! I love that! I\'ve had this unit since last December and I often remove the carafe for my first cup before it\'s done brewing. Still no drip. So that, combined with all the other convenient features about which you\'ve already read in the other reviews, make me happy with this purchase. I\'ve gone through many coffee makers in my 30+ years as a coffee drinker, and this is the best one I can remember for the price.'),
(2311, 5, 1, 3, '2015-05-16', 'Right after return window expired the warming burner began to ... Right after return window expired the warming burner began to rust.  Now a month later its entirely rusted.  Makes my high end kitchen look sloppy.'),
(2312, 7, 3, 5, '2016-04-15', 'Works great. Easy to clean up. Delivers the best tasting coffee.'),
(2313, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-15', 'Great, but not the best. I have been a long time fan of the kcup style machines for a quick one cup of coffee. There were a lot of times when my family would make an entire pot of coffee only to waste the full pot. Also with varying taste preferences among family members the individual pods are great! So far I love this coffee maker because t also had the option to make a full pot if you wanted. However, there are a few downsides I have found that causes my rating on this specific coffee maker to not be a full five stars.  not every type of kcup works with this system. We kept getting error codes saying the pod would not work. From what I\'ve read there\'s a new technology in the cups. Not sure why they changed this aside from limiting you to buy \"keurig\" brand cups. One upside is they do say they will replace the ones that don\'t work with ones that do. I have yet to contact them to see how that works though.  the pot does not come with this so you have to purchase it separately. Some of them do, just depends on the seller, which I also find odd. I also had hoped to just use an old coffee carafe I had left over, but you can\'t. You have to use/purchase the keurig carafe. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I also received compensation/product for my unbiased review.'),
(2314, 6, 1, 4, '2015-02-06', 'Some what uneven toasting, also a standard Thomas english ... Some what uneven toasting, also a standard Thomas english muffin will not eject high enough to grab it without burning yourself.'),
(2315, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-22', 'A Best Buy for the money Nothing Fancy. Just makes coffee. And the Price is right. The removable water tank is a great feature. One of my best purchases ever.'),
(2316, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Great coffee maker This coffee maker is great. Really like the water reservoir being removable;no more mess.'),
(2317, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-22', 'Hard working unit with a small footprint. Great little unit that can toast 4 pieces of toast at once.  The unit also bakes and broils.  The house stays a lot cooler es. using the kitchen range.'),
(2318, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'Five Stars Perfect'),
(2319, 3, 1, 4, '2016-09-13', 'Four Stars VERY NICE, EASY TO USE, PRICE IS OK.'),
(2320, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Nice! This is a great toaster oven for the money.  I have found that I need to adjust the temperature higher than is called for, but it works great.  It is a compact size that fits in my cabinets, but it is large enough to cook almost anything I want.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(2321, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-27', 'I like that you can lift the handle up to get ... Yay toast!  What else do you say about a simple home appliance that works as it should.  Put bread in the slot, push the handle down, and in a couple of minutes you get toast.  I like that you can lift the handle up to get smaller items like mini bagels without needing to stick a knife in to get the bagel out.  It takes a little playing to get used to the settings (level 1-5, bagel, defrost) but once you do it works fine.  Items come out pretty even - one side gets a little more done than the other but that seems ok.  You have to hit the cancel button to get the toast out manually - pushing up on the handle doesn\'t work very well.  It\'s got a three year warranty, so I hope it lasts that long. I seem to need a new toaster every year or two, I bought the Cuisinart in part because the warranty and in part because my other Cuisinart appliances (coffee pot) have been reliable.'),
(2322, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-19', 'Four Stars Very good to make fruit juices quickly and eficiently'),
(2323, 6, 1, 3, '2016-02-13', 'Folks, believe the claims that it can\'t toast a piece of bread evenly on both sides What\'s up with \"Cuisinart?\"  Either Cuisinart has given up actually making things and lives by licensing its name or it has a problem with quality control. I wanted a simple white toaster.  I thought the \"name\" might overcome the complaints about uneven toasting. But the thing really cannot toast two sides of the same piece of bread at the same level.  You would think that was the very least that a toaster, even a cheap one, would do. I reduce the \"cook level\" and that minimizes the toast-on-one-side-charcoal-on-the-other-side thing but it also minimizes the \"toasting.\" I\'ll keep it but I sure won\'t recommend that anyone buy it.'),
(2324, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-25', 'Five Stars My mother in law just loves it.'),
(2325, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-20', 'Great deal for a great toaster! I am loving this toaster!  It cooks wonderfully and for the price, ya just can\'t beat it.'),
(2326, 2, 1, 2, '2016-02-29', 'Two Stars cheap product'),
(2327, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'So far so good. I have had this coffee maker for about a month now. Having NO problems with it, no leakage, no burning coffee, nothing.  After reading the reviews before I bought it, I\'m knocking on wood.  So far so good.'),
(2328, 3, 1, 5, '2014-08-01', 'Excellent all-around toaster/convection oven Perfect for a single person or couple, the oven works great.  It\'s easy to program and use, and does a thorough job when used as just a toaster, or as a full-bore oven or convection oven.  Yes, it does get warm when in use, but to me, that\'s just Common Sense.  I\'ve always trusted the Black & Decker name when it comes to toaster-ovens, and this one doesn\'t disappoint.  Great buy at a great price!'),
(2329, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-16', 'It\'s good. I love this Keurig. My whole house uses it. Easy to keep clean. However, I wish the instructions for the filter and all of that would\'ve been more clear! Overall, I\'m satisfied.'),
(2330, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Five Stars Works just great...'),
(2331, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-24', 'I liked my older one better but this one works fine I liked my older one better but this one works fine. Just don\'t like the way the dials are set up.  I do endorse Black and Decker, I guess I should have spent more money and bought a better one.'),
(2332, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Husband Very Happy! So far so good with the coffee maker! My husband loves the ability to make the whole container and dispense one cup at a time...without drips most of the time. No more messy pouring from the pot!'),
(2333, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-23', 'Five Stars WORKS FANTASTIC!!'),
(2334, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-12', 'Best coffee maker ever Best coffee maker ever! For everyone who loves the convenience of just pouring one cup at a time... But needs more than just ONE CUP BREWED!!'),
(2335, 10, 1, 4, '2016-10-18', 'Good for the price This product worked well for a few months, but ultimately the small motor inside began running at less than full power due to daily use. For the price, I was OK with that and bought a Ninja as a replacement. I would recommend letting your fruit thaw slightly and chopping it into smaller pieces before putting into this blender, it will extend the lifetime of the product greatly.'),
(2336, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-28', 'Five Stars Works good'),
(2337, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'Cuisinart Toaster Got here fast.  Nice size for a 4 slice toaster. Works like a charm. Just what I wanted!'),
(2338, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-11', 'LOVE IT! Easy to use!!! I almost cancelled the order for this coffee pot but, glad I didn\'t. I was concerned with the so called short cord. One review said, it was literally 2 inches....I had to laugh when I saw the cord it was tucked nicely in a hide away hole so you actually need to PULL the cord OUT of its hide away hole so, it actually is 28 inches long ! Cord is no issue at all outlet nearby and I don\'t need to unplug ever! It is BIG nicely fits uner my cabinet. It does perk loudly other than that it great. My husband can actually work it too (he isn\'t very techy) I programmed it for him he just puts coffee and water in the night before and wakes to the coffee aroma.Mmmmm. it\'s ready BEEP IS tooo LOW and it has E for empty and F for full just like fuel gauge in a car to show how icu coffee is available wish that was in cups these two are my only negs. If you want a travel sized cup you simply pull to edge of counter remove drip pan and filler up. No leakagevyet.it does recommend cleaning it with vinegar n water and filter change I guess if you don\'t do THAT one could have issues :/'),
(2339, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-19', 'my wife loves it so I\'m happy. little tip my wife loves it so I\'m happy.  little tip, if you like your coffee really hot, let your coffee sit for about 10 min on the hot plate before pouring your cup.'),
(2340, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-23', 'Perfect! Fantastic coffee maker. Brews quickly and consistently, doesn\'t get fouled by hard water easily and is easy to clean. The carafe doesn\'t drip either!!'),
(2341, 2, 1, 3, '2015-03-04', 'Works fine but wish it had an on and off button Works fine but wish it had an on and off button..once you set timer, you have to wait it out..nuisance'),
(2342, 2, 1, 2, '2016-07-10', 'Two weeks and it caught fire Only had it two weeks before it caught fire and melted.  The controls on this unit make it difficult to set the time.  No precision.  So if you set it just a little too high, it will kill whatever is inside.  If you decide your toast is done and want to turn it off, you have to force the timer back to zero which feels counter intuitive as it feels like you\'re breaking the unit.  I think this product is potentially very dangerous.  I don\'t recommend it.  If you do get it, don\'t leave it unattended for a moment.'),
(2343, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-10', 'Super fast delivery and great CS Totally thrilled with my purchase. Super fast delivery and great CS. Highly recommend.'),
(2344, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-26', 'Cheap + Looks Good + Works Well = All You Need I use this product to bake polymer clay and for heating any craft related products that I use for my etsy shop. Pros: Looks great Works well Easy to clean Cons: Power cord is very short, it\'s wayyyy too short for an appliance but it\'s not an issue for me. I really like this toaster oven much more than the one in my kitchen, will be ordering another one as soon as my kitchen toaster oven fails.'),
(2345, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-16', 'I have owned this toaster for several weeks. So ... I have owned this toaster for several weeks. So far, I have not had any trouble with it. It works as it should.'),
(2346, 11, 1, 2, '2014-07-12', 'Nice little toaster oven, but not good quality materials. The features are okay, and it\'s nice and small, although I would prefer an inch bigger, as some of my \'toaster oven\' casserole dishes do not fit. The deciding factor was that the rack/tray rusted when I washed them once. I\'ve long been a toaster oven chef and this is my 3rd toaster oven in the past 8 years. I\'ve never seen one rust and I like to be able to wash the removable parts.'),
(2347, 8, 1, 4, '2016-09-07', 'pretty good coffee for the money Broke zojirushi 5 cup zutto pot and only replacement is the manufacturer site at $30 probably add another $10 for tax and shipping.  Thought this pot might work but it does not - although zojirushi filter holder can rest on this pot and fits in the zojirushi body. Now for B&D.  It needs a flat bottom filter.  #2 cone filter from zojirushi, when flattened, can handle about 3 scoops of coffee ground.  I made 2 cup coffee and the quality (taste, heat) is about the same as zojirushi.  B&D operation is about the same and cleaning up as well.  I can buy 3 B&D for one zojirushi and if I break the next one I already ordered, I think B&D will be a serious contender.  Zojirushi is about 4 years old and still working as if new.  I can\'t say for B&D longevity, and will keep it for emergency times. Only weakness I see (trying new) with B&D is how the handle attaches to the pot.  Metal ring on the bottom is good, but the top is held with less than 1/8\" of plastic which may snap sometime in the future.  The plastic fit of the total machine is pretty good but the thin body parts don\'t build confidence.'),
(2348, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-31', 'Great toaster oven I LOVE my toaster oven.  I gets a lot of use. I have baked pies, bread, meatloaf, and use it for toast every day. I love the fact that it\'s quick and doesn\'t heat up the kitchen.'),
(2349, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-22', 'Five Stars Perfect for my office ! The price was a plus!'),
(2350, 10, 1, 2, '2015-05-18', 'I recommend putting in a little more money to get something ... This blender is what you pay for...a cheap temporary fix that won\'t last very long. I recommend putting in a little more money to get something that will last longer. I used this blender last summer and it lasted me a whopping 2 months. It doesn\'t do a very job blending too much produce, but is good for a simple smoothie.  It also makes scary noises when trying to blend ice....'),
(2351, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-29', 'Good cooking Dash good looking! Bought this in the warehouse deals  it only had a teeny tiny dent on the top of the unit but I saved a lot of money and it works beautifully. Product was exactly as it was described.'),
(2352, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-20', 'Best product for the price. Perfect size/performance - previously disappointed with B&D product. Perfect fit for the counter top - easy to use - need to \"tweek\" toast settings to meet your taste.  Made well and well priced'),
(2353, 2, 1, 4, '2016-07-20', 'Handy Works well for the price.  Have to watch the toast closely so as not to burn it.  Bottom knob requires firm turn to adjust.  Like the versatility of having a small, efficient oven.'),
(2354, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-02', 'Huge improvement over my old Keurig K45 Our first experience with Keurig was the K45 I bought my husband several years ago, and I hated it. The coffee was weak and the machine broke and had to be replaced. Twice. This little Keurig is such a HUGE IMPROVEMENT. I have cleaned and put away our regular drip maker, hopefully for good. What I like about Keurig in general is the lack of dishes to wash. I am a stay at home mom during the day but I work at night, usually until midnight. I\'m not really in the mood to wash my coffee carafe and filter basket at 12:20am, and even less so when I crawl out of bed with the kids at 7:00. What I like about this particular Keurig is the \"strong\" setting. It makes a great cup of coffee, tastes just like drip, with the reusable K cup filled with the coffee of my choice. It\'s almost too strong, like the coffee at Starbucks, when I use the strong setting with the Peet\'s Alma De La Tierra organic dark roast K cups I bought at Costco. I think the whole proprietary K cups thing is pretty lame and I don\'t have the time or interest to sit around hacking stuff. I also prefer to use my own coffee to save money, keep plastic out of the landfill, and improve the variety of coffee available for me to use. I took a chance and ordered these reusable K cups and they work great.'),
(2355, 12, 1, 3, '2014-09-13', 'Good toaster- poor oven The popup toaster works OK. The toaster oven is more like a broiler, and overdoes the top of whatever one is trying to cook. You also need to clean out bread crumbs, etc. after each use, or the unit  while in the oven mode will turn on your smoke alarm. Cleaning is  hard to accomplish.'),
(2356, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-30', 'Four Stars I\'m happy with it!'),
(2357, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-18', 'Great Little Coffee Maker Perfect coffee maker, it makes 2 bigger coffee cups worth of coffee which is just about what I need during the day. It brews quickly, and quietly. I wish it had a timer on it but for the price I am not complaining. I am very pleased with this coffee maker.'),
(2358, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-28', 'Excellent toaster Warms quickly, toasts to a golden brown, cooks evenly.... I now wish that I had replaced my old one long ago.'),
(2359, 11, 1, 5, '2015-08-08', 'It fits large breads well, which is what I ... It fits large breads well, which is what I needed, and toasts evenly.  If you leave it sitting under the heating element when it turns off, it will continue to burn your bread so you can\'t leave it.  It doesn\'t bake as well as a convection toaster oven.'),
(2360, 8, 1, 4, '2016-07-27', 'Four Stars Just perfect for one person.  Fist small coffeemaker that I liked.  The price couldn\'t be beat!.'),
(2361, 1, 1, 1, '2016-05-19', 'What a joke!! I wish I could give it zero stars. This thing dispenses a loogie\'s worth of coffee no matter what option I press. Also, it drips water the second I turn it on. What a joke. Never buying a Keurig again.'),
(2362, 9, 1, 1, '2016-03-23', 'DON\'T TAKE THE BAIT!!!! As a household with two serious coffee drinkers we bought the Cuisinart DCC-3000 thinking we could finally have the best of both worlds with on demand coffee and no expensive K cups. The reviews were either glowing or nightmare worthy but the decision was made to give this machine a try.  We followed the instructions to the letter and found this is a seriously lacking machine. Oh, and that doesn\'t include the fun, mad dash, \"honey, grab the towels!\" moment when we realized our countertop was covered in water from the machine.  You can\'t fill the reservoir for multiple uses...measure it to exactly how much coffee you want or you\'ll have watered down almost coffee. The 1-4 button is useless on this machine. Most of our travel mugs, a must for the working coffee drinkers who want their morning ritual on the run, do not fit. Novel idea, horrid execution. Needless to say, within two hours of receiving it the machine is back in its box and the return label is printed. Don\'t waste your money!'),
(2363, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-25', 'Five Stars This is so ideal for all my family to use!!!!!'),
(2364, 9, 1, 4, '2015-01-10', 'Good Coffee Maker The product is very sturdy and value for money. The machine is easy to use and fits in well into my kitchen.'),
(2365, 7, 3, 5, '2014-08-22', 'Only had it for a week, but so far so good.'),
(2366, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-23', 'Great little mixer Great little mixer! I purchased to make protein powder drinks & it really mixes well & has a lot of power! would def recommend!'),
(2367, 7, 3, 5, '2016-06-10', 'I am very pleased with my Flex Brew. It works well with any of the k-cups. Regular coffee grounds comes out too watery for me. Nice small fit on my counter.'),
(2368, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-11', 'Great Coffeemaker! I love the fact that you don\'t have to lift the carafe that\'s full of water and pour it into the coffeemaker. It has a container that is attached to the back of the coffeemaker. You just lift it out, fill with water and place it back into the slot. I also like the little wheels on the bottom which make it easy to turn and move around. You have the option to change the temperature, and how strong you want your coffee. The clock and timer are a nice option also. It takes about 8 minutes to brew a full pot, which isn\'t too bad. It\'s so quiet, you don\'t even know it\'s brewing until it\'s almost done. I love my new Hamilton Beach Coffeemaker!'),
(2369, 3, 1, 1, '2015-11-23', 'My original post on this product was that I love it, because I loved my original one My original post on this product was that I love it, because I loved my original one. However, I sit not even 3 months later with a product that doesn\'t work.'),
(2370, 1, 1, 2, '2015-08-20', 'Keep your older model this one is not worth the purchase I am surprised at all the positive reviews for this product.  I have had an older Keurig which had to be replaced once because of a malfunction and Keurig replaced the model with no issues.  This time we wanted an upgrade and a smaller model, so we bought the K250 2.0.  I have been completely  disappointed with the purchase.  Keurig worked hard to develop a system that prevents you from using other pods but left off simple conviences of not having to adjust your cup size every single brew, not allowing more than 4 or 6 oz\'s for hot water and having a max size of 10 0z.  Who in the USA drink a 4 or 6 oz anything?  My coffee mug and my tea mug are the same so instead of giving me the same options I have to brew twice to get hot water for tea. Yes its smaller and takes up less counter space but removing and replacing the water reservoir is a pain, especially if the unit is located under upper cabinets. I am sorry but design and features of this model make it a miss and I would not recommend.'),
(2371, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-30', 'I love, love, love this machine! I drink coffee all the time - morning, noon, and night, so I am always reheating the coffee, and many times end up burning it and just dumping the pot. This lets me do my individual cups one at a time, hot and fresh every time. I like that it has the filter basket and the \"K\" cup insert, but I have not used the \"K\" cup insert because I think that all of the brands of \"K\" cups are too expensive, so I really don\'t know if the attachment works, but I don\'t see why it wouldn\'t. The regular brew and bold brew options are good, as I like my coffee strong and the rest of my family likes a regular brew of coffee. They love it too. The coffee maker right next to it is almost never used anymore, unless there are several people who want coffee at the same time. I also used it to make hot cocoa, but put the cocoa packet in the cup, as the basket cannot be filled that much, but it also came out great. The only negative - and this was my fault - is that if you put too much coffee in the basket it will make a mess - but the enclosed instruction booklet said just that, so it was my fault, not the Flex brew. I would recommend this to anyone who likes a good cup of coffee!'),
(2372, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-13', 'Great automatice coffee pot I purchased this to replace a Keurig. It has several brewing choices, I would buy this again.'),
(2373, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-28', 'but this newer one cooks food real good in less time what ever the box says I owned the old version of this oven. it lasted me 8 years and still works. but this newer one cooks food real good in less time what ever the box says: its true.'),
(2374, 9, 1, 3, '2015-09-29', 'Buy the Warranty, You\'re Going to Need It I\'m the kind of person who\'s very demanding about equipment performance and always does my part by maintaining it properly. I really do wipe down and dry out my coffee machine daily and clean out the system monthly with a vinegar/water flush. So when a failure occurs, it bothers me. A lot! I love just about everything this machine this machine offers. It has enough features and adjustments for the average coffee drinker: fast and quiet, programmable on/off, 1-4 cup brewing option. It\'s beautiful and I like the design of the removable reservoirs for both water and coffee. Here\'s how this machine has disappointed me: 1)  The clock function stopped working within a few months. Ironically, I could still adjust the auto on time, but I could no longer adjust the time of day (it\'s on a different setting). Not a big deal until daylight savings time... 2)  Yesterday the coffee reservoir drained out onto the counter. The cause doesn\'t appear to be a clogged coffee filter or improperly placed reservoir. Not sure what the cause is, but it\'s intermittent. I\'ve brewed three pots of coffee since yesterday morning with no issue. Unfortunately, this problem is substantial enough for me to get rid of the machine. Being late for work due to cleaning up a mess from a leaky coffee machine is unacceptable. 3)  Short warranty period. Judging from the reviews, Cuisinart is well aware of this issue yet the warranty period is very short. 90 days I think. I\'ve had my machine for 10 months so I\'m out about $70. Very frustrating considering coffee machines generally last years. If you decide to purchase this machine, purchase the 3 year warranty. You\'re going to need it.'),
(2375, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-27', 'Five Stars very nice for my needs.'),
(2376, 12, 1, 1, '2015-08-17', 'Better to Buy a Toaster and a Toaster Oven Separately Tried it once and it worked. Tried a second and it didn\'t. Had to return. I thought the compact, two-in-one design would be a good idea, but both the toaster oven and the toaster are mediocre and do not have enough space. Toaster oven would barely hold two slices of bread, let alone anything else like a small TV dinner or a bagel. The retro look is cute but is overkill with the quality of the actual device.'),
(2377, 7, 3, 5, '2014-01-12', 'I really loved the coffee maker simply because it is not only a coffee maker! The reason I only gave it a \"good\" on the durability is because its a coffee pot; how durable can they be? But I love it. I love how I can make tea in one cup than a cappuccino in the next. IT IS GREAT! So far, I haven\'t had any problems out of it. P.S. Don\'t judge me on my \'nickname\' it was when I was in middle school when I came up with that... I\'m a third year in college now.'),
(2378, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-08', 'Breakfast is not possible without it. Nothing beats toast, eggs, and beacon for breakfast. This helps me make amazing toasts!'),
(2379, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-29', 'Five Stars excellent coffee maker!!!!'),
(2380, 6, 1, 5, '2014-06-16', 'thoughts for cuisinart coffee maker and toaster The Cuisinart coffee maker is exactly what I wanted (in the right color for our new kitchen renovation) and the toaster is just fine as well.'),
(2381, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'your toast with this one. very nice piece of toaster well design and fast'),
(2382, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-16', 'Love my Keurig K250 2 Love my Keurig K250 2.0. brewing system. Like having fresh coffee and tea when ever I want.  I was skeptical weather or not my Dad would like it, but he also likes the fact in a few seconds fresh coffee in your cup and it easy for him to use that is a bonus! Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(2383, 12, 1, 1, '2014-09-20', 'Horrible Cheap, crappy toaster. the toaster OVEN is too small for a slice of bread. Pointless.'),
(2384, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-08', 'just like an oven The way of cooking from this product is more likely functions of an oven.'),
(2385, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-11', 'It\'s exactly the size that I wanted It\'s exactly the size that I wanted for two people. Quality is good. I\'m happy with this purchase.'),
(2386, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-14', 'Excellent coffee maker We love this coffeemaker for many reasons. One of which it makes hot coffee, our last one was never really that hot, especially after I add creamer. Another is a no drip pouring spout, it works awesome with, that\'s right NO DRIP! All the features on this coffeemaker are great, I hope it lasts for a good long time.'),
(2387, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-03', 'Best Toaster Oven for the Price Awesome buy, completely exceeded my expectations. It toasts my turkey clubs super fast, and looks sleek too. All in all I got a very good toaster oven, at a very good price!.'),
(2388, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Love it!! Hi, I\'ve had my Keurig 2.0 since the beginning of May 2015.  I had an older model for a few years and loved it.  I enjoy my 2.0 Keurig just as must!  The only disappointment I had, was not being able to use up some of my older K-cups that I previously had with the older model. Apparently the new 2.0 won\'t take all K-cups.  I believe if the K-cups do not say Keurig brewed on them they will not work. Other than that I love it!!!!! Whether for coffee, or water for tea or hot chocolate!  I would highly recommend it!!!'),
(2389, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-05', 'Five Stars its a toaster and it works real well, no complaints...'),
(2390, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-07', 'This is the BEST thing EVER This is the BEST thing EVER. Our oven stopped working and we didn\'t have the cash to buy a new one. We purchased this in hopes we can continue to bake and make our oven meals. This is such a good product, I am no longer looking to replace my oven. My husband was constantly burning food because he forgets to check it. He no longer burns meals or baked items because of this handy timer function, that also shuts the unit off. Its used frequently, I bake cakes, pizzas, casseroles, roasts, and it toasts bread beautifully. If it ever breaks, which it doesn\'t seem like it will any time soon, I will be purchasing another.'),
(2391, 6, 1, 5, '2016-09-17', 'Good toaster. Replaced a 2 slice Cuisinart Use it almost daily. Good toaster. Replaced a 2 slice Cuisinart. We love their products.'),
(2392, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-25', 'Excellent simple toaster Heats up very quickly, and cooks surprisingly evenly despite only a single element in the middle across the top, and single element at the bottom. Keep this on my desk at work and use it almost daily.'),
(2393, 2, 1, 1, '2015-03-09', 'but had we not been in the room it could have been much worse. We have a defective and dangerous product We bought this a couple weeks ago to replace our handy Black and Decker that was with us for a decade. Even on the medium-low setting it routinely burns toast. This morning it ignited a piece of bread during toasting. We put the fire out, but had we not been in the room it could have been much worse. We have a defective and dangerous product.'),
(2394, 5, 1, 2, '2015-09-03', 'Love that you can take the water tank off to ... Love that you can take the water tank off to fill. This is our second one. The second one lasted less than 3 months.'),
(2395, 6, 1, 4, '2014-12-18', 'So far so good! Needs a couple rounds of toasting at full ... So far so good! Needs a couple rounds of toasting at full power for homemade bread to get golden brown.'),
(2396, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-22', 'Good so far! I read some reviews before buying. I\'m on day 2 of using it. Here\'s what I\'ve got. * It\'s CLEAR this won\'t last long with frequent use. I\'M fine with that...after all...it\'s only $20 * It gives off an odd smell when running...almost like burning plastic. Goes away immediately. * I cut everything into small pieces. The blades are tiny. I also bought ice try that makes tiny cubes. Normal sized would be a terrible idea. This next part is really IMPORTANT...it seems to ha e difficulty pulsing if you just have it set down. At first I kept stopping to rearrange things inside and then pressing the button again. Too annoying for me. Since its light weight...I just pick it up and shake it while pulsing. This works out great. That\'s everything. I\'m doing a 30 day juice challenge. So it\'s going to get heavy use. I will post an updated review in 28 days :)'),
(2397, 5, 1, 1, '2016-02-17', 'One Star went to pay for it 39.99 & price jump to 60.99 what\'s up !'),
(2398, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-26', 'Very Pleased We have had this product about 2 weeks and so, we are very pleased. it is easy to use, easy to clean, easy to set up in PM for AM brewing and the coffee has been very well brewed. It has more adjustments to temp and blend than I have had before and I do really like that. Also it is easily swiveled to remove or access the water chamber, so works well under a cabinet. Finally, and most exciting, it does not leak when pouring from a full carafe!!!!!'),
(2399, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-17', 'accidental purchase I\'m sure it works fine but I don\'t recall ordering it so it was a shock to discover that money was taken from my account'),
(2400, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-06', 'One Star Motor for 2 blenders burned out within 90 days.'),
(2401, 3, 1, 1, '2016-05-10', 'I do not like this product. I will only state that I do not like this oven at all.  It does not even work. See the photo. (Amazon would not let me tell you the real reason why I gave it a one star review)'),
(2402, 5, 1, 1, '2016-01-23', 'This coffee maker is garbage. The second day I had it This coffee maker is garbage.  The second day I had it, the face plate that surrounds the clock and the controls fell off.  Attempts to reattach it were futile because the plate either would fit right or would fall off all by itself whether the coffee maker was on or off. Today, six weeks after it crossed my threshold, it just quit working.  The power button was on, the element was on but it never brewed coffee.  It is now residing in a recycle bin awaiting its fate. If this is any indication of the present quality of a formerly reputable company, its future is dim. Don\'t waste your time--or your money'),
(2403, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-06', 'Love it! Love this toaster oven!  So happy that this oven works so well and that it saves me from using the big oven so much.  Plus being able to use a 12 inch pizza pan in it is a great bonus!'),
(2404, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-05', 'I considered buying a Keurig because liked the idea of being able to make just one cup of coffee when I wanted it. The Keurig machines cost much more and I didn\'t want the cost of buying K-cups. This was the perfect solution for me. There are 4 coffee drinkers in my house and we are all able to have a fresh cup of coffee when we want it with out breaking the bank. We use the filter basket with our favorite brand of coffee most of the time. We still have on occasion bought k-cups for a different flavor. The machine has worked well either way for us. The machine does not have a large water reservoir so there are no settings for the size of cup you want. Just add the amount of water you need and chose between the regular or bold selection. This will make a cup up too 14oz. I find myself haveing an occasional cup of coffee during the day more than I used to because it is so easy and convenient.'),
(2405, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Five Stars everything perfect no problems, thank you very much. The preferred user. THX'),
(2406, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'toaster It can toast, its very functional as compared to all of the toasters I have owned in the past'),
(2407, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Fastidious Toaster When it has came down Black & Decker and what they have offered from irons and blow dryers, t small appliances they have worked well, but they have at times worked a little too well where it can be too good for words. That has been the case with their Deluxe Stainless Steel 4-Slice Toaster Oven. It works well, but at times works a little too well, where it can work faster but can also overdo toast easily. But it does deliver very good browning and warming for pizzas, baked goods and reheating with ease. It can deliver well as much as the higher-end brands like Krups and Cuisinart. I found it very to deliver after some time, and works nicely for the dollar. If you want a beginner hi-speed toaster that works for the dollar in energy and value.'),
(2408, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-12', 'It works more like a pulse feature on a food processor I thought I was getting a cheaper alternative to a nutribullet for making smoothies.  There is, however, no comparison.  I don\'t know if it is a lack of power or the design, but it doesn\'t move the ingredients around enough to mix from top to bottom.  I had (bought another nutribullet), to manually use a rubber scraper to move the ingredients.  Also, you have to hold down the button to operate the blender.  That is a weird design feature.  I don\'t usually stand around and hold a blender for it to work.  Normally I make smoothies in the morning, while my nutribullet is blending I can do other things to get ready.  You can\'t do that with this blender.  It works more like a pulse feature on a food processor.  I gave this blender to Goodwill.  A good example of how the cheap can become expensive.'),
(2409, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-07', 'Five Stars Good'),
(2410, 4, 1, 2, '2015-05-31', 'Warped heating element after 1-year, stay away, fire hazard After having this unit for over 1-year, I noticed that the heating element was warped showing a bright glow like glowing lava.  This definitely looks like a fire hazard surprised the product isn\'t recalled, looking and the questions and answers thread there are a lot of consumers having the same issue.'),
(2411, 7, 3, 1, '2016-01-18', 'This product was very difficult for me to use, so I tried their Customer Service number for advice. I was unable to get any help because I was unable to give them the product\'s serial number. This is embossed in teeny, tiny black letters on the black plastic bottom of the coffee maker and my 80 year old eyes (even with tri-focals) simply could not read them. So it\'s back to the store to return the coffee maker and save my money until I can buy something better than Hamilton Beach.'),
(2412, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-14', 'Great value for the price! I confess to being surprised by the high quality of this reasonably-priced toaster oven. Though it does reflect a lot of heat, it does the job of baking very efficiently. And, amazingly for a toaster oven, it actually toasts thoroughly and well! I would have given 5 stars, but for the heat it throws off.'),
(2413, 5, 1, 4, '2015-01-22', 'Good quality Having this as a programmer is really a biiiiiiig help. This is my partner on staying up late. Coffee == codes.'),
(2414, 3, 1, 4, '2016-02-03', 'buttons could be a little better but overall very happy with works very well, buttons could be a little better but overall very happy with oven'),
(2415, 8, 1, 2, '2016-04-16', 'Two Stars Broke within a few months.  The generic one I had from walgreens lasted over a decade.'),
(2416, 11, 1, 3, '2014-06-09', 'Ok for the intended purpose. Great price but lacking in quality of build. Nonetheless this is my third version of this item so there must be something good about tie.'),
(2417, 9, 1, 1, '2016-06-18', 'Buyer beware leaking product! This machine started leaking just after the return date. Would you not know many many communications with the company with no luck. This products works one date leaks the next or good for two days then leaks. I\'ve cleaned the machine as they have instructed. Still no luck. So far the seller so far has said my problem. Well after cleaning the mess 5 out of seven days For the last two weeks I\'m done with my expensive counter being flooded with coffee and me working to remove the stain. The amount of coffee lost could pay for Starbucks everyday with no clean up. Who knew.'),
(2418, 6, 1, 3, '2014-10-01', 'An Okay toaster. Just okay.  Bagel setting does not work.  Toasts evenly.'),
(2419, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-17', 'Good! Small, convenient, easy to use. This was a great choice for my small kitchen with not much counter space. Best part is the price tag!'),
(2420, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-27', 'Great product So far, so good!  We have had this brewing system in our office for the last two months.  Picked a Keurig so that everyone could individually brew their preferred beverage.  The product is super easy to set up and comes with spare parts for regular maintenance.  I really like that you can specify if you like the coffee stronger, or if it is a beverage other than coffee.  The little screen on the front is also nice, easy to read and easy to use.  Will update this review as time goes by and if we notice any changes.'),
(2421, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Excellent! We like to cook in the Toaster over ... Excellent!  We like to cook in the Toaster over during the summer and I has worked perfectly!'),
(2422, 12, 1, 1, '2016-05-26', 'all were wonderful but the last one I have bought 4 of this toasters,  all were wonderful but the last one.  Cannot close the door completely and most of the time can\'t open Had too long to return.  My loss!  Two were gifts and were great'),
(2423, 12, 1, 3, '2014-02-17', 'Just needs one thing In the movie \"City Slickers\" there is a line about life being \"Only one thing\". On this item the one missing thing is a timer. The device that closes the taster top should be elsewhere, in it\'s spot should be the slider for how dark you want the toast to be and the knob under the slider should be a timer for the oven. I don\'t even know why they bother with the temperature knob. It\'s a toaster oven, not a roaster oven. In order to get anything done in a timely manner you have to crank the sucka all the way to 600 and watch it like a hawk. Otherwise it\'s heat/cool/heat/cool until you want to tear out your hair! I\'d say this is not a toaster oven for a new bride or a kid in college. This one requires a chef! (or a mom that\'s been around a stove or two.'),
(2424, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-05', 'great buy! The best protein shake maker ever made! Great for the price. Me and my friend we both use it three times a day and rely on it after the gym - it\'s an amazing little thing'),
(2425, 10, 1, 3, '2016-02-22', 'Three Stars Not sturdy enough for true raw veggies.  I would say this blender is only good for soft fruit smoothies.'),
(2426, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-16', 'Five Stars great brand great value'),
(2427, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-01', 'So handy! I use this puppy every morning for my breakfast shake.  It\'s just protein powder, peanut butter, coconut milk and ice so I don\'t know how well it does with fruit but it blends the ice just great.  It\'s so compact which is perfect for my small apartment!'),
(2428, 5, 1, 4, '2015-07-19', 'good deal Another great buy'),
(2429, 7, 3, 2, '2015-05-11', 'I was very excited to try this as I usually only make one cup of coffee and was wasting so much with a regular maker. I first tried it with the make amount of water and used cold water like it says, the coffee was weak and cold. I tried it again with less cold water and better strength but still cold. and the today I tried with bold setting and hot water and still the coffee was cold but it did smell great compared to the first two times. Every time I use this I have to warm up the coffee in the microwave. I am not sure why it comes out cold regardless of the water temperature and I found nothing in the instructions that was helpful. I think this is a good machine in the way it works minus the coldness of the coffee. It brews fast and the bold setting seems to be what works best in my experience whether it was ground coffee or a k-cup, I used both, just wish I didn\'t need to heat up the coffee after it just finished brewing.'),
(2430, 5, 1, 3, '2015-05-20', 'Does what it says, but the pour lip is ... Does what it says, but the pour lip is too small. Every time I try to pour a cup of coffee when the carafe is full it spills over the edges.'),
(2431, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-02', 'Very Nice maker. Bought a $20 maker but lasted only ... Very Nice maker .  Bought a $20 maker but lasted only 6 months . I figured that\'s what happens when you buy something cheap . So hoping this will last a few years .'),
(2432, 4, 1, 2, '2015-03-16', 'Two Stars Too complicated to set temp/time.'),
(2433, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-10', 'Fabulous Coffeemaker!!!! WOW! I LOVE this coffeemaker! It is replacing a second burned out Bunn! Totally user friendly as mu husband set it up! The coffee is nice and hot and although not as fast as the Bunn, for the number of features, you can\'t go wrong with this coffeemaker! I use normally 4 scoops and I used the BOLD setting. I can now cut to 3 scoops and use that feature to save on coffee. Plus you can program it too! Simple!! Great buy! Will see how long it lasts. Thanks Hamilton Beach as you have a great product here!'),
(2434, 5, 1, 3, '2015-02-28', '13 Month Machine Purchased this model because of the great reviews and I would generally have to agree. The machine brews good tasting coffee at a decent speed and price point. The variable temperature on the burner is also nice feature. The two problems: Number one, it no longer works. Lasted 13 months. Brewed approximately 500 pots and then suddenly stopped working. Number 2, it vents steam out of the top as it brews, damaging the underside of the cabinet. It had to be pulled out on the counter for each use and that was kind of a pain, especially if other food prep was going on. I wouldn\'t recommend this machine. It cost about $0.09 per use based on what I paid and I think there are better options in this price range.'),
(2435, 4, 1, 3, '2016-08-23', 'as promised. god for about 2 years, normal ... as promised.  god for about 2 years, normal for a toaster.'),
(2436, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-22', 'Very annoying and tends to over-toast unless on lightest setting Smallest one I could find for plain toaster oven.  Clean lines - in reality more black than chrome (only front is chrome).  Generally works well, but my biggest gripe is that ALL the toaster ovens now have a dial to start toasting.  \"Turn past 10 then back to setting desired\".  Very annoying and tends to over-toast unless on lightest setting.  Just have to watch closely if toasting bread with a spread or butter or melting cheese on something.  Otherwise basic functions work.'),
(2437, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-28', 'oven perfect results and perfect size'),
(2438, 3, 1, 5, '2014-07-17', 'Five Stars It does what it supposed to do. Works great'),
(2439, 3, 1, 4, '2016-10-31', 'Really large capacity but outside gets VERY hot Very large capacity made this a great substitute oven while our kitchen was being renovated. Now that that\'s done, we use it for smaller cooking, when it\'s more efficient than heating the \"real\" oven. PLUS SIDE: Auto oven shut-off on timer (defaults to 30 minutes, but can be easily changed). You can\'t forget and leave it on accidentally. Convection baking - yes, it reallys works in this small oven. Makes really great toast - though a bit slowly (big oven rack makes six standard slices easily) Easy to clean, removable bottom tray. Easy to use controls. MINUS SIDE: It\'s VERY large - measure your space before buying. The top gets REALLY, REALLY hot when in use - not good if in reach of children. Minor point - the \"beeper\" is fairly quiet, so it\'s hard to hear if you\'re not in the room with it.'),
(2440, 3, 1, 3, '2016-03-25', 'The door does not close very tightly but seems to ... The door does not close very tightly but seems to cook OK.  I dropped the crumb tray and it cracked in the front. Don\'t know if a replacement is sold.'),
(2441, 4, 1, 4, '2016-04-03', 'Toasting is a little uneven. Good little oven but tends to scorch my toast or takes 2 times to toast it if I turn down the level to medium. Great timely delivery at the holidays.'),
(2442, 7, 3, 4, '2015-12-29', 'It works great and looks good.'),
(2443, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-03', 'keurig 2.0 review I really like this Keurig 2.0 it was a birthday gift and I really love it! my husband and I use it everyday. We dont go out for coffee as much at all anymore.'),
(2444, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-01', 'Have had it for only a short time, but ... Have had it for only a short time, but so far it has done all we\'ve asked of it--good toasting, backing, broiling, and warming.'),
(2445, 1, 1, 1, '2016-09-22', 'Normally Keurg are great, but not this model for sure No mater what you do, there are to many coffee grounds in the bottom of your cup.  Normally Keurg are great, but not this model for sure.'),
(2446, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-10', 'Four Stars Small fingerprint on the counter and works well.'),
(2447, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-07', 'Can\'t beat the heat for the price Works great, versatile, looks good, well made. No complaints after 3 months of almost daily use.'),
(2448, 4, 1, 2, '2016-11-14', 'Bought this toaster oven for one purpose... ... Bought this toaster oven for one purpose...  to make toast.  Unfortunately, this oven does that poorly. It is inconsistent in how dark it makes the toast - very inconsistent from time to time.  Also, inconsistently toasts each piece of bread - darker underneath and towards the top of the bread.  I\'m burning more bread than I\'m eating!  I\'ll have to replace it.'),
(2449, 11, 1, 3, '2015-01-10', 'This is a fine toaster oven save for the fact that when using ... This is a fine toaster oven save for the fact that when using the toast function, it could use a little more control on the timer.  There is a very small sweet spot on the dial between \"untoasted\" and \"charred\".  As a small oven, though, I have no complaints.'),
(2450, 7, 3, 5, '2015-11-05', 'We loved it so much we replaced my grand daughter\'s Keurig single serve machine with this lovely Hamilton Beach. We have other coffee makers that are Hamilton Beach and we have used it for years and love it too.'),
(2451, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-13', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker, for an unbeatable price.'),
(2452, 4, 1, 2, '2016-07-20', 'Never again Hard to read knob settings. Cuts off to frequently. I\'m waiting for it to die just so I can buy a better product!.'),
(2453, 11, 1, 4, '2014-10-03', 'Four Stars Very good, even toasting'),
(2454, 5, 1, 2, '2015-12-25', 'Two Stars bought this Jan 2 of this year and it quit working on me today.  Very disappointed'),
(2455, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-02', 'I love this toaster oven. BEST PURCHASE EVER. Honestly as a college student, I think this was the best thing I had decided to buy. Although I would say a traditional toaster toasts bread better than this oven... this has many more uses. Pizza bagels, Pizza rolls, Frozen dinners, Frozen breads. Honestly it\'s a little unhealthy because it encourages me to not cook my own meals, but it\'s beautiful on the run. Also, I use it to heat things up when I don\'t want to use my old gross microwave. It looks really sleek and nice in my kitchen However, the con is that the top of the oven gets really HOT. I thought it was insulated to keep the heat in. I had a little produce scale on top while it was on and it totally melted the bottom of it! So be careful and you should be good.'),
(2456, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-04', 'Good Toaster Oven for the price Lets be frank, its a toaster oven.  If you want Great evenly toasted toast, bagels, or whatever, buy a good toaster. And if you are making a pot roast or souffle use your oven.  But, if like myself, your kitchen space is limited so whatever gadget can pull double or triple duty like this toaster oven, for the price you can\'t go wrong. It works every bit as good as one that I had years back that cost 4 times as much.'),
(2457, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-31', 'The best! I love this toast station!  It works beautifully for our needs and doesn\'t get too hot to the touch like so many toaster ovens.  This is our second one it works like a gem, last one was about 7 years old.'),
(2458, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-09', 'wonderful coffee Great product with best tasting coffee'),
(2459, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-01', 'Great little blender for the office. Awesome little blender I use to mix my protein shakes at work. Simple to clean, simple to use. I don\'t know how it is to mix harder things. But if you are just using this to make some protein shakes for the gym it\'s excellent.'),
(2460, 7, 3, 5, '2014-03-08', 'Bought one for my aunt . She saw mine and liked it so much I gave it to her for a birthday gift. I like the idea of being able to use my own brand of coffee. It is easy to clean and store away when not in use.'),
(2461, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-27', 'Nice product ! I Love it! Nice product! My friend recommended and I\'m fascinated! It does what it says and you can customized the heat and the time!'),
(2462, 4, 1, 2, '2015-05-29', 'I would NOT recommend this product for the simple fact that it doesn\'t ... I would NOT recommend this product for the simple fact that it doesn\'t have a timer. My old toaster oven that we got at Big Lots and lasted over 10 years had a timer which made the user experience very nice.'),
(2463, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-19', 'Best cup of coffee in years!! Absolutely love it!! Easy to use, easy to clean, and awesome to get a cup of fresh coffee with the push of a button in stead of the old heavy  carafe of burnt up coffee.'),
(2464, 2, 1, 2, '2015-10-07', 'Step up and buy yourself a nicer toaster oven. Not this one. This toaster oven is \"meh\". The bread toasts VERY unevenly and it doesn\'t stay hot (wanted to bake jalapeno poppers for 25 minutes at 450F- the heating element turned itself off after 10 minutes and the poppers were not crisp). Spend a few more dollars and buy yourself a nicer toaster oven. Mine is being donated to charity.'),
(2465, 7, 3, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Love this coffee maker. I read some bad reviews and I was a little skeptical about buying it, but it is perfect for me. If you follow the directions, you should have no problem making a great cup of coffee every time. The only downside for some people may be that the is no reservoir for your next cup of coffee, must put water in each time you use it. I don\'t like to leave my coffee maker plugged in when not in use, so this was not an issue for me. I would suggest that you don\'t pour water directly from cup into the back, as it could spill, I use a measuring cup with a spout to make it easy. Have already recommended this product to family members, I have had it about 2 weeks'),
(2466, 6, 1, 3, '2016-02-06', 'Not evenly toasted Does not toast both sides of bread evenly.  One side darker than the other.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(2467, 6, 1, 5, '2014-03-10', 'Great product! This product was everything that was stated in the discription. I would recommend this to anyone interested in a toaster!'),
(2468, 3, 1, 1, '2015-10-28', 'Don\'t guy it Not good gave it away'),
(2469, 3, 1, 4, '2015-09-11', 'Good stuff I\'m very pleased with this with one exception.  the quality of the broiler plate seems substandard.  But otherwise, a really good kitchen appliance.  I\'m sure I can find something of better quality, perhaps a small porcelain broiler pan that will be more durable of better quality.  But I like the way it works and it\'s nice to cook in it instead of heating up the whole oven when you\'re cooking for one or two.'),
(2470, 6, 1, 1, '2016-04-21', 'VERY Disappointing toast results I am so disappointed in this toaster. I loved the look, the size, the features, yatta, yatta, yatta, but when it comes down to toasting - yuck. It can almost burn one side but just warm the flip side of the bread. Very uneven. The heating wiring doesn\'t work uniformly.  SO - NO MATTER HOW YOU LIKE THE LOOK OR THE PRICE - pass this one by. If it weren\'t past the time I could return this, I would. What a disappointment. IF the maker had focused on the primary purpose of this unit, it\'d be perfect. As it is, it\'s not.'),
(2471, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-10', 'Five Stars good hot coffee'),
(2472, 9, 1, 4, '2015-07-04', 'Four Stars great coffee maker at a great price. ordered it on a Sunday and it arrived by Tuesday afternoon'),
(2473, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-05', 'Decent toaster oven for the money - good buy !!! Simple and effective toaster oven that works pretty good for what it costs. :-)  Thanks to the other folks before me who recommend this unit. I noticed the one we have the timer switch is easier to turn verses another one I tried at a local Walmart.  The lighter twisting one is much easier to adjust your darkness IMHO.  Work wouldn\'t allow me to spend the money on a nicer one so this was my only option. ;-)'),
(2474, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'Looking Forward... This is a high quality design. I look forward to the morning knowing this will be my coffeemaker.'),
(2475, 10, 1, 2, '2016-02-23', 'Works fine until it doesn\'t I liked this when I first got it, even though it had a bit of trouble actually blending frozen fruit (whole strawberries are a no-go), but today it suddenly stopped working! Two days ago it was perfectly fine, blended up my morning smoothie no problem, today pressing the button does nothing. I tried different outlets and everything, it just quit for absolutely no reason. Would not recommend.'),
(2476, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-12', 'Perfect!! Perfect!!!  We have been using this toaster for over a month.  No complaints.  We haven\'t use our oven since purchasing this toaster.'),
(2477, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-10', 'Does a good jub. Does a good jub.'),
(2478, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-26', 'I needed a small, individual, coffee maker for upcoming guest. This model was dependable, made a great cup of coffee, and versatile. I have nothing but good things to say about this model. Thumbs Up!'),
(2479, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Well Thought Out Design Very good quality. Nice wide slots. Easy to read settings. I like the way the buttons light up. Does not really take up much more room than my two slice toaster did. I love the feature of lifting up, no more burning my fingers.  I am very pleased with this toaster. I will update later if anything changes. Update: Its been three months and still works great. Push down buttons have broken in now and are easier to push down. Toast slots are mostly even, but sides of bread are not toasted exactly the same, just slightly different. I am still very happy with the quality, function, and size of this toaster. I really like the cancel button, good design idea. Overall, a great investment.'),
(2480, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-13', 'Excellent coffeemaker! Have tried many through the years as ... Excellent coffeemaker! Have tried many through the years as have many of us but I have to say this is the one! Keeps coffee hot and does not seem to get too strong even if you let it sit in there for awhile. Love the ease of use. The water comes out easily to be filled in the sink the basket pulls out easily and brews excellent coffee. I read a lot of reviews before buying this so I thought I would write one of my own because I love it!'),
(2481, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-10', 'Five Stars This is great'),
(2482, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-14', 'Awesomeness Works great, should have gotten a toaster oven sooner in life...'),
(2483, 2, 1, 4, '2015-06-14', 'Perfect function but user/human interface needs improvement I baked some fish when I got it. The fish turned out as good or better than my regular gas oven would do. It heated up to 425 in 2-3 mins. Toasts better than my old toaster, even with the bottom of the bread slightly darker as the heating element is on the bottom. I used a little less than half way. The control knobs are hard to read which may be an issue for older folks or people with poor eye sight. Also, operation is somewhat convoluted. You have to get used to setting knobs in the right position before setting the timer. Lastly, the knobs require guessing. The temp knob, for example, goes from 400 to 450. If you need 425, you have to guess. It\'s the same with toasting. Even considering the flaws with the knobs, this toaster oven functions beautifully and is a bargain for $30. I\'m thinking of getting my parents one as well.'),
(2484, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-25', 'I replaces one I had prior and fine for simple toasting and grilling No nonsense. I replaces one I had prior and fine for simple toasting and grilling.'),
(2485, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-31', 'Five Stars Does everything I expected plus some, If I had to list a con it would be that it could do with a slightly longer power cord'),
(2486, 10, 1, 3, '2015-02-08', 'Great price For the money it works allrigt'),
(2487, 12, 1, 2, '2014-02-20', 'good but small It is alot smaller then I thought it would be but over all good the door will not stay closed but customer care was good about getting another one'),
(2488, 3, 1, 3, '2015-07-11', 'disappointed Biggest disappointment is that the rack  does not pull out when you open the door, which flops down when opened.  It used to have knobs which are much simpler to use (and control) than the current selection of identical buttons.  And why do they insist on using beeps that are \"nails on a blackboard\" sounds to sensitive ears? And I don\'t think it is possible to keep the outside (which gets EXTREMELY hot ) clean. All that said, it does the jobs required of it.'),
(2489, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-31', 'Great coffee maker.  Love it. Excellent coffee maker.  Had others and didn\'t like them.  This doesn\'t drip when you pour your coffee.  Easy to run and clean.  Love it.'),
(2490, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-23', 'First Keurig Purchase This is the first Keurig product that I have purchased and I am very happy with it.  I have hesitated to buy a Keurig system because of the price and the increased price of the coffee.  However, I got a good deal on the brewer and I also bought a reusable pod.  I love having a hot cup of coffee within a minute having a choice of several flavors available.  It is very easy to use and the coffee tastes great.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2491, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-10', 'Fairly fast at Toasting Had bought a big (KitchenAid)oven, but it took forever to toast a bagel, almost 15 minutes....so returned it and went with this B&D toaster oven.  It toasts extremely well and fairly fast, so quite happy with the purchase., My only complaint is the ticking it makes when its toasting, but very happy with the purchase.'),
(2492, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-10', 'Five Stars Works great. Would order again.'),
(2493, 5, 1, 2, '2016-06-02', 'The reason I don\'t like it, is I haven\'t been able to use ... The reason I don\'t like it, is I haven\'t been able to use it yet!  The first one I ordered was broken, and it was replaced with another one that was broken.  The panel above where the coffee filter pops out is held in by two screws and the panel was snapped off in both of the ones I received. It looks like a great coffee maker with some nice features, but I would like to be able to actually try it.  I haven\'t had coffee for a week now and I am a little irritated! If I get one that is not broken, I will then review that one.'),
(2494, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-29', 'This was perfect for both of them and they use it every ... My daughter and her college roommate couldn\'t agree on a toaster or a toaster oven and they don\'t have much space in their small NYC dorm for both.  This was perfect for both of them and they use it every day.'),
(2495, 5, 1, 3, '2016-05-02', 'Average Unit We have had many coffee makers from very expensive to cheap ones. This one is not really a super product. The carafe dribbles when you pour coffee. We have only had this unit almost a year and the timer quit on it. Other than that it is a fairly decent unit.'),
(2496, 3, 1, 4, '2015-08-11', 'Great performance, cooks and toasts food well Pros: Great performance, cooks and toasts food well.  High quality construction, and heats up quick. Cons: Input controls on the front of the unit controlling cook time and temperature are poorly designed and difficult to read.  Each button press is accompanied by a sharp high pitched beep.  Could have been improved to meet the quality of the rest of the unit.'),
(2497, 11, 1, 3, '2014-05-11', 'Weird Toaster Zoom in on the dials in the photo... you actually have to turn the top dial past 10 and back down every time you want to make toast!  Other than that stupid design flaw, the thing has been great and works well.'),
(2498, 2, 1, 3, '2016-10-06', 'Not the best toaster but not the worst It\'s okay.  Not the best toaster but not the worst.  It\'s a fair product for the price.'),
(2499, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-30', 'Five Stars LOVE this little coffee maker.'),
(2500, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-17', 'Four Stars Pretty good toaster oven, functions as described.'),
(2501, 5, 1, 2, '2016-04-02', 'While it makes perfectly serviceable coffee, this is not ... While it makes perfectly serviceable coffee, this is not the coffee maker for someone who enjoys the subtle nuances of small batch roasted coffee. You must choose whether you want 1-4 cups, regular, or bold; you cannot choose 1-4 cups AND bold simultaneously. I\'ve played with all 3 options and none is helping me brew my ideal pot of coffee. Also, within 2 weeks of owning the machine the front face plate has popped off (and continues to pop off) when opening the basket door.'),
(2502, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'got to love cuisinart. shipping missing basket to Taipei up date from 3 to 5 stars. got to love cuisinart. shipping missing basket to Taipei. 6 stars if i had um :)'),
(2503, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-12', 'Four Stars Good.'),
(2504, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Five Stars This lil coffee maker is great'),
(2505, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-10', 'Great Purchase! So pleased with this little item. Perfect for me! Took the place of my older toaster. Looks great on my counter too.'),
(2506, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-25', 'Four Stars So far it is excess get expectations'),
(2507, 2, 1, 2, '2016-08-13', 'The handle is very close to the top of the ... The handle is very close to the top of the toaster and it is difficult to avoid burning your hand on the toaster.'),
(2508, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-23', 'Perfect! I was able to used this thing for my leftover food. Perfect oven for food heater.'),
(2509, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-21', 'Arrived really fast and is easy to use Arrived really fast and is easy to use. Working great!  It does produce stripes on the bottom surface of the toast though if that is a concern for you.'),
(2510, 1, 1, 1, '2015-06-29', 'which is fine by me I am not at all impressed! I owned the older version which wasn\'t brewing very quickly even after cleaning so I decided to upgrade. I used to use my own coffee and add nutmeg or cinnammon to the grounds, there are no reuse able cups to fit this I also had bought kcups and apparently because they were \"older\" they wouldn\'t work in the machine. When we called Keurig we were told we would be reimbursed for the amount of coffee/ tea that wasn\'t able to be used in the machine and to go online and a credit would be there. Needless to say I have yet to see a credit and have been using a cheap table top coffee maker, which is fine by me!'),
(2511, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-19', 'Five Stars very useful if you don\'t want to turn on a whole oven!.'),
(2512, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-01', 'Five Stars Awesome oven. Bought it refurbished and it looks new.'),
(2513, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-25', 'Five Stars easy for averything.'),
(2514, 5, 1, 3, '2014-12-29', 'We were very disappointed in the temperature of the coffee even with the ... Our Cuisinart was it getting old so we thought we would treat ourselves to a new coffee maker. We shopped online looking at the various brands and styles. The one thing that attracted us about the Hamilton Beach was the large blue clock on the front surface and removable water reservoir which we found to work well. We were very disappointed in the temperature of the coffee even with the temperature adjustment in HIGH coffee would only be warm not hot. We returned the coffee maker and reordered another Cuisinart Model 1200. It was twice the price but now we can enjoy our morning coffee.'),
(2515, 5, 1, 1, '2014-05-28', 'Worked great for 35 days. Dead on the 36th day. Supposedly you can send it back to the manufacturer at your shipping cost and they will replace it. Might go to Walmart instead and just buy a different one.'),
(2516, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-01', 'Five Stars Great design for using less space. Works well and has great features'),
(2517, 5, 1, 1, '2016-03-27', 'Junk The faceplate for the display came off within days of purchase. Wrote to the company and received no response. Took ten minutes to perk when we bought it.  Five months later it takes thirty-five minutes to perk a pot.  This is the second one we\'ve purchased with similar results.'),
(2518, 8, 1, 5, '2015-01-24', 'Best coffee maker for the money In the last year, I\'ve had many coffee makers including the K cup machine and I keep coming back to this one.  Glad I didn\'t throw it out. I think it has to do with having a paper filter.  The coffee seems to taste better and I can make more coffee with it.  You cannot go wrong with this coffee maker and the price is right.'),
(2519, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-20', 'Makes great coffee. Easy to use Makes great coffee.  Easy to use.  The removable water reservoir and the wheels under the base that enable the coffee maker to rotate are very handy.  The operation is intuitive and the buttons/switches are well made and should stand up under regular use.'),
(2520, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-25', 'As advertised... Perfect for those (like me) with limited counter space that want the convenience and speed of a toaster (compared to a toaster oven) PLUS the convenience and efficiency of a toaster oven (compared to a conventional oven).  Just be aware that the oven in this unit is slightly smaller than a standard toaster oven, and the single slot in the toaster oven can only hold one over-sized slice of bread (if you like those fancy bakery style loaves).'),
(2521, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-23', 'Five Stars great, thanks!'),
(2522, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', '... had this same model 10 years ago and o loved it. Found it on Amazon and bought another I had this same model 10 years ago and o loved it. Found it on Amazon and bought another.  Very good product.'),
(2523, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-13', 'Its perfect for making a single serving smoothie or shake just had to buy a new one after about 8 years of use on the first one i bought.  Its perfect for making a single serving smoothie or shake. love it'),
(2524, 8, 1, 2, '2016-04-27', 'I wish I\'d gone with the better init in the first place This is a no feature pot, as expected from the description. If stopped working properly after only three months. I replaced it with a $20 Mr. Coffee. I wish I\'d gone with the better init in the first place.'),
(2525, 8, 1, 4, '2016-02-04', 'Four Stars MAKES A PRETTY GOOD CUP OF COFFEE FOR A NO FRILLS POT'),
(2526, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-07', 'Great price, great machine Great coffee maker. Great features, we are pleased. Swing out basket, removable water container,fast brewing and great coffee. You won\'t be disappointed.'),
(2527, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love the Keurig K250 2.0 I absolutely love this brewer! I used to have the keurig mini which was always nice, but the K250 2.0 quickly make a cup of coffee and give you the option of how big of a cup. It\'s also nice to have the water resivore instead of having to fill everytime you go to make a drink. I would recommend the Keurig K250 2.0 to anyone looking to buy. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2528, 4, 1, 1, '2015-05-28', 'Worked for a couple of years, and then the heating coil split Worked great for about 3.5 years, and then the main heating coil split and began to emit a hellish orange glow around the warped coil and is no longer usable. The unit was cleaned and taken care of throughout its short life, so I assume this is just due to the normal heating and cooling process. But as others have noted, the limited warranty does not cover this far. I\'d recommend it as far as you know that you\'re paying $70 \"marked down from $145\" for something that is not intended to last past three years. I had thought Cuisinart was one of those brands that lasts forever (or at least more than 3 years!), but this shows me that that\'s not the case.'),
(2529, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-12', 'JUST WHAT I EXPECTED It is a good little toaster oven.  I finally had to replace my old one after many years of service. This one is great for the money.  It is small so it fits on my counter space.  It is almost as good as the one I replaced. The one thing different is the size of the baking tray (smaller than the old one) and the glass door does not open all the way.  it is on hinges and you have to be careful when you take the tray out.'),
(2530, 6, 1, 4, '2016-03-16', 'good Very much pleased with my purchased'),
(2531, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-31', 'Great heat but ok quality I had purchased this at another retailer due to a special pricing and I love it. It is absolutely useful for heating up bread and leftover pizzas or frozen fries. I have also tried baking cookies (yes, raw cookie dough) with this oven and the cookies turn out great. The oven heats up quickly, so I only let it preheat around 1-2 minutes before I start putting my food in. There are lots of modes and may seem complicated, but it really isn\'t. The first button is used for setting temperature, while the second one is for oven settings such as broiler, bake, and toast. The last button is for the timer. I also love the removable crumbtray that is placed at the bottom of the toaster; you can easily pull that out  and dispose of any remains that may have fell during the baking process. The baking tray that came with this oven is a major concern though. It is so flimsy and thin that my tray already has browned spots on it after multiple use. It\'s even worse because I use aluminum foil to cover that tray every time I use it, but it still has a brown spot. It is also way too small such that I cannot hold a lot of food in it, thus causing me to have to split my baking into 2 batches. I\'m only able to overlook this because of the great heat setting and the pricing of this product.'),
(2532, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', '... keurig for my dorm room and so far I love it. I just have to find k cups ... I decided to buy a keurig for my dorm room and so far I love it. I just have to find k cups that I really love. Other than the problem of finding just the right k cup I love this machine. Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(2533, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Keurig 2.0 Had always wanted a Keurig, and then i saw the 2.0 and i thought why not. Still enjoying the newest addition to my kitchen.Not only does this heat up within seconds the coffee says so Hot... two added bonues. Easy to purchase products online if needed and when i contacted Keurig direct not only was their customer service extremely helpful but they also sent me a free product. Now that is what Customer Service is All about...\"Thanks,Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(2534, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-18', 'Easy to Use & Clean Easy to use & clean.  Love the \"wheels\" on the bottom making it easy to roll out from under the cabinets.  I like the plastic reservoir eliminating the need to fill a container & then pouring it in.  Compact.  Good temperature.  My husband doesn\'t need to put his cup in the microwave as he did with our old coffee maker.  The only reason I didn\'t give it 5 stars is that it will only stay on 2 hours and not 4. Added Photo to show the incremental markers on reservoir.'),
(2535, 5, 1, 3, '2014-02-08', 'Coffee not hot We\'ve been using this coffee-maker for 3+ months now. Coffee tastes OK, but has never been hot. Need to microwave it if you want hot coffee. Now the front panel keeps falling off, exposing the electronic controls. Panel won\'t stay on. Will probably look for a replacement soon.'),
(2536, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-16', 'Finally, a toaster to get excited about My attitude toward toasters has always been that they are all unreliable and inconsistent, so get the cheapest one you can.  That worked and I had my last no-name toaster for 10 years until one of the spring mechanisms would not stay down.  After getting a cheap Sunbeam from Target that I hated, I decided to shop Amazon.  This toaster had good reviews, and the pricing was a really good deal.  I gave it a try and returned the Target toaster the next day.  At last, I have found my dream toaster.  The settings give consistent toast color and dryness, and the defrost setting lets you toast frozen bread in one cycle.  I have also used it for baguette, and it did a great job.  Could not be happier with this toaster.'),
(2537, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'Five Stars runs well and delivered promply'),
(2538, 5, 1, 2, '2015-02-02', 'Broke in less than 9 months!!!  GRRRRRRR Bought this April 2014 and it worked great...a little slow, but we loved it.  January 2015 it worked one day, then nothing the next!  Still has time display, but water won\'t drip and burner doesn\'t heat up.  I am an un-caffeinated, grumpy, coffee-less customer!'),
(2539, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'Five Stars Great product!'),
(2540, 4, 1, 5, '2016-12-05', 'Five Stars lasts a really long time.'),
(2541, 5, 1, 4, '2016-06-15', 'Delicious Coffee, Wimpy Labels This makes great coffee, very tasty and hot! Digital interface is easy to use as is the water & filter container. My only gripe would be the on/off label has worn off (the only label to do so) - maybe I just make a lot of coffee, but that seems like a button they should make sure can really take the abuse of people that are half-awake & in need of caffeine!'),
(2542, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-05', 'Good One! Works great and coffee is really good'),
(2543, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-05', 'Inexpensive & works like a charm. Simple & cheap. I usually only drink 1-2 cups a day and this size works well. Simple to use.'),
(2544, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-09', 'Five Stars I love this coffee maker ,I use it everyday !'),
(2545, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-06', 'Keurig K250 This is my second Keurig and it\'s better than the first one!!!  I was a little disappointed that the color looks more \"pink\" than \"purple\" compared to my other purple appliances.  I also find the off button is difficult to use.  I have to use my fingernail only to get it to shut off!  Love that I can brew just water and also that it makes a 10 ounce cup of coffee!.'),
(2546, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-14', 'The bomb These are great for single serve smoothies and milkshakes. Powerful enough for a $20 blender. Like others say, go easy on the motor or you will burn it out.'),
(2547, 6, 1, 4, '2016-12-26', 'Good toaster. We wanted a simple, 2 slice toaster with wide slots to fit our limited counter space.  The feet are tall enough to allow the cord to not interfere with how the toaster sits.  The controls are easy to get familiar with and does toast and frozen waffles without a hitch.'),
(2548, 12, 1, 4, '2014-10-08', 'Good size. I like that it is a toaster ... Pros: Good size.  I like that it is a toaster and mini oven all in one appliance. Cons; English muffins tend to curl or sometimes fall to oven level.'),
(2549, 7, 3, 2, '2016-05-26', 'coffee has A bad tast'),
(2550, 4, 1, 3, '2015-07-11', 'I like most all of the toaster except the the three ... I like most all of the toaster except the the three control knobs could stand to have a somewhat more raised edge to be able to recognize the selected setting more easily.  This could deasily be done for litterally pennies.'),
(2551, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Great product We use it almost everyday.  Cooks evenly, cooks quickly, cleans up easily.  Would purchase again.'),
(2552, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'Five Stars Shipped very fast. Works we\'ll.'),
(2553, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-17', 'Best Ever! This is the BEST coffee maker ever! The wheels make the roll out from under the cabinet easy and convenient. The back reservoir removes easily to fill at the sink faucet and not have to fill with the pot. The pot is perfect!!! No and I mean no more drips or spills, the plastic lip is spill free!  I would recommend this coffee pot to anyone and everyone!'),
(2554, 7, 3, 5, '2015-07-01', 'this little coffee maker is so good.. i had a keurig but it started leaking water, got rid of it. Took a chance, and bought this, I am so happy that I did, I can use my keurig k cups, and i can also just use the built in basket that comes with it!! Would definitely recommend this product.'),
(2555, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-08', 'Great value. Not exactly for making super smooth margaritas ... Great value. Not exactly for making super smooth margaritas but great for smoothies & shakes. Used for salsa & pie crust, also.'),
(2556, 6, 1, 3, '2015-03-17', 'Uneven toasting - sometimes Love the size, look, and features of the product.  Unfortunately, some of the heating elements did not work some of the time.  Very episodic as with one piece of bread, a large section of heating elements didn\'t heat up and with another piece, another time, they all worked.  Very uneven toasting when not working and too unreliable.  Returned for replacement in hopes the next one will work well. If the elements worked all the time I would have given it a 5* review.'),
(2557, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-13', 'Great for the price. This is a very nice and inexpensive toaster. It is perfect for bread or frozen foods when you need it done fast! Clean up is very simple as the toaster comes with a pull out insert at the bottom which can easily be wiped off after use. The only downside is that it does not always toast completely evenly so you have to keep an eye on things to avoid burning. In general however, it gets the job done at a great price!'),
(2558, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-18', 'Five Stars Best coffe maker for the money.  Get one!'),
(2559, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-17', 'Five Stars Right size for our needs.  Works well.'),
(2560, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-31', 'Five Stars Works exactly as advertised.'),
(2561, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-25', 'Toast We - the wife - love it. We\'ve toasted waffles, bread and lots of bagels. Setting work fine. Good product so far.'),
(2562, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-19', 'Glad I went ahead and bought  it! (i have a blender AND shaker cups but love this!) I am so glad that  I bought this! I DO own a blender and shaker cups..but this is super great for when i want to mix protein powder with a a few other ingredients (creatine or aminos etc). The other awesome perk is that its actually PINK! A lot of products are advertised as bright pink and show up an ugly mauve color. I am super pleased and am going to leave this out on my counter for quick shakes, etc.! I am going to buy some for family and the black one for my boyfriend too. It\'s so inexpensive and helpful.'),
(2563, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-09', 'great value A real good creamer melts well.'),
(2564, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-14', 'Five Stars works great'),
(2565, 2, 1, 4, '2016-06-03', 'Four Stars Works great!'),
(2566, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Good toaster oven Naysayers fugg off. This is a good toaster oven and beats anything you\'d buy for the same price or less. Make sure you know what a toaster OVEN does and you\'ll be satisfied.'),
(2567, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-04', 'So far so good. It seems to work well So far so good.  It seems to work well.'),
(2568, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-04', 'Four Stars The toaster works good'),
(2569, 10, 1, 3, '2015-06-02', 'Decent small blender So I\'ve had this blender for about 4 months now and it works fine. It will blend my smoothies (yogurt, juice, ice, fresh berries) fine, but it doesnt\' really cut up frozen fruit very well. There is also a faint burning smell that happens if you\'re blending for more than 10-15 seconds, which is kind of concerning.'),
(2570, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love my keurig This is my second keurig brewer. I love the convience of always having water ready for coffee, tea , hot chocolate. I also got the carafe with my brewer. I have not used it as of yet. The ease of setting this up and using is wonderful. You can choose different sizes of cups and strenght which is always nice. The brewer is a little loud when water is going into a cup but not overly loud. We use this for hot water to make oatmeal. works great. I recommend the keurig coffee system to anyone looking for an easy to use good brewing cup of coffee. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(2571, 4, 1, 2, '2016-10-27', 'and I join the others who are disappointed with Cuisinart We have had this for a few years now, and I join the others who are disappointed with Cuisinart. It BURNS the toast very time, even on the lightest shade setting. It would incinerate the bread if put on medium. All we want is a good basic toaster that melts cheese on our toast and rewarm things from time to time. It seems very tough to find these days, with all the manufacturers adding fancy features and complex electronic controls that do nothing but break.'),
(2572, 5, 1, 2, '2016-02-12', 'Grinds in my coffee! I\'m very disappointed with this purchase. I\'ve only had it for about a month and I am already seeing grinds in my coffee - I am using quality filters so not sure of the cause of this - and so soon after buying it! I was hoping to get a quality coffeemaker and thus far, have not experienced that.'),
(2573, 4, 1, 3, '2016-03-25', 'I\'ll Buy a $30 Anything Else Next Time I\'ve always relied on Cuisinart and I loved this toaster oven until very recently - the door began to catch and the only way to get it open was to grab an oven mitt and hold the top of it while jerking on the door. Last night, it just plain would NOT open, and while trying, a plastic lid slipped off and landed inside the (HOT) oven...It\'s still there, as no amount of pushing, lifting, tugging and pulling on the door would open it more than an inch. Pulled the crumb tray out, and of course, the lid is too thick to come through that opening. The oven is useless as it is now, and I\'m very disappointed. Because if it weren\'t for the door, I\'m sure it would still be operational. (sigh) Planned obsolescense at it\'s best, I suppose. Too expensive to have that happen!'),
(2574, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-01', 'I love very hot This coffee maker differs from the one I use in my office. I use this one at home because it favors the way I drink coffee at home. I love very hot, strong coffee, but I drink about 10--12 quarter cups over the course of 4 hours. If I pour a half or full cup, it goes cool and I wind up pouring out half a pot or more. This coffee maker stores the coffee in a heated reservoir for 2 or more hours, and I quarter-fill my cup by pressing on the dispensing tab. The coffee stays hot at least 2 hours, and probably for 3 or more. There is a meter above the tab that shows how much remains in the reservoir. Even at 3 hours the coffee is hot but does not taste warmed over or boiled down. The water reservoir can be removed to fill at the refrigerator. The coffee reservoir and the cone filter basket have handles to remove them for rinsing or washing. I have not used the programmed start, but coffee is ready in under 6 minutes. It takes a \"cupcake\" paper filter. It comes with a gold foil filter that I have refused to wash, much preferring to transfer the grounds in the paper filter directly into composting. I\'m quite happy with my purchase. In fact, I bought two. My son loves his too.'),
(2575, 11, 1, 2, '2014-04-27', 'disappointment the toaster oven is difficult to control the darkeness of the toast. but the oven bakes really well. i love how crisp the pizza crust becomes. another dissapointment is the overall size, it is really large. if you don\'t have much room on the countertop this is not the oven for you. .'),
(2576, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker!  Stays very hot and easy to program.  5 stars!!'),
(2577, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-26', 'So far so good! I have veen using it for about a week. This is the first coffee maker i have ever bought! It\'s fast and easy! Set up is easy! The only weird part is i accidentally bought pods that werent k-cup approved but it still brews the coffee! Not sure if that is a good thing or bad thing.'),
(2578, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-20', 'Not bad for the price Not bad for for the price,  works pretty darn well in smoothies and shakes.  I keep mine in desk at work, drink a 100 calorie shake instead of the sweets everyone brings in.  I do use crushed ice and pulse it.'),
(2579, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-11', 'awesome machine. Makes great coffee and has terrific features Wow! awesome machine. Makes great coffee and has terrific features.. best coffee maker we have owned yet - bar none.  The cord was a real head-scratcher (just bad design on an otherwise perfect machine). Hubby plugged it into a power bar and we were off and running - no brain bender there folks... just a reasonably good power bar makes this the best coffee maker on the market today.  Hubby is getting used to the gold coffee filters - he\'s still wondering why his old stand by coffee tastes so much better :-)'),
(2580, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-17', 'Love this toaster oven Love this toaster oven! The first arrived dented, but I received a replacement without a problem. Does a wonderful job.'),
(2581, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-18', 'Works great for a small coffee pot Works great for a small coffee pot. Keep it in my office at work. Can produce 2-3 cups of coffee.'),
(2582, 9, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Love it! No coffee pot to break and it ... Love it!  No coffee pot to break and it works great!'),
(2583, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Great for work Replacement coffee maker was cheaper than buying a replacement carafe.'),
(2584, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-09', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker.  Easy to handle.'),
(2585, 9, 1, 4, '2015-12-09', 'Good Buy. Love everything about it but the water filter fits into the machine in such a manner that it is useless. Have only had it a few days but it looks great and seems to work well.'),
(2586, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-15', 'Five Stars Works well and easy to use.'),
(2587, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-03', 'Nice and Useful Small Oven This is a handy, time saving little oven.  It is perfect for reheating or to quickly bake/broil small items like frozen biscuits, Texas toast, cinnamon toast, etc.  The instructions call for several minutes warm up before using.  We\'ve found that it takes very little time, especially if you\'re using the broiler setting.  The instructions are pretty good for explaining how to use the oven.  The controls are all analog knobs, no displays.  They work fine.  The provided accessories are adequate to get started. + Toasted items come out with a better crispness than the conventional oven + The regular toaster is better and faster for just toasting bread. + It\'s the perfect size for two people.  More servings will need a larger size. + It does get very hot to the touch so be careful, especially around kids'),
(2588, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-20', 'Five Stars best coffee maker ever......small foot print ...easy fill....great price....would buy again'),
(2589, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-05', 'Five Stars Best coffee maker I\'ve had since my last Cuisinart.'),
(2590, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-12', 'I love the design I love the design. I took the advice of the one guy that wrote a real good review.  I especially love the removable reservoir that I can fill at the sink and snap in place again.  Unfortunately, lately, after @ 1 year, the reservoir is causing a problem.  The coffeemaker sputters and spews steam instead of brewing coffee.  I read other reviews and found the problem identified as either the need for cleaning or the reservoir\'s seat.  Cleaning didn\'t help but when the sputtering starts, I can remove the reservoir and slam it in place and it will make the pot of coffee.  It\'s a shame because otherwise I consider it to be perfect.  I will probably disassemble it and try to identify the problem further and probably break it.  Update: Success! I took it apart and found the problem. A semi-hard deposit like a little whitish stone formed in the intake tube and blocked the incoming water.  Note: I have well water. That explains why some people say cleaning works and some say slamming the reservoir in place works... both would work.  They really don\'t want you taking this apart.  It has four screws in the bottom, one of which is a security screw needing a special flat screwdriver with a notch in the center.  The intake tube is orange and is held in place by mini hose clamps.  I took the end of the tube off nearest the reservoir opening.  When I did the little \'stone\' fell out.  I guess I\'m good for another year.'),
(2591, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'toaster oven Exactly what I needed, great quality and great price'),
(2592, 6, 1, 4, '2016-10-24', 'Four Stars Good quality prompt delivery.'),
(2593, 10, 1, 2, '2015-01-04', 'The quality gets worse every time we buy one of these The quality gets worse every time we buy one of these.  This one the plastic mixing cup lasted about 6 weeks & split all the way up the side.  Was always hand washed & never dropped.  The first one of these I had lasted 3 years with daily use.  The last few have not lasted 6 months & the warranty stinks.  They want you to pay posatage to return & for the replacement.  By the time you do that you\'ve paid for another machine'),
(2594, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-25', 'Five Stars Works well, makes a decent cup of coffe.'),
(2595, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-22', 'great coffee maker easy to use with the wheels on bottom and removable water container it can be used in it\'s own space on counter, the carafe is the best pouring with no dripping of coffee, love it; makes good coffee also.'),
(2596, 12, 1, 2, '2017-01-23', 'Bottom line the toast did come out fine; but with the safety concern being a prime ... I feel it\'s a safety concern, one is the oven control knob doesn\'t shut off by it\'s self has by older toaster oven had,the other concern when you use the toaster the crumbs from the toast fall into the oven I found it igniting inside the oven had also smelling up the kitchen where my wife complained from the other room.  Bottom line the toast did come out fine; but with the safety concern being a prime member had it sent back. PS the wife hated it.'),
(2597, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-12', 'Five Stars Perfect coffee maker that is DRIP FREE, easy to use and makes superb coffee. Well worth $50'),
(2598, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-06', 'This coffee pot works great . I needed a smaller machine since I am the only one that is home .Now I can make a small cup or a bigger travel mug . The move able shelf works good , make sure it locks in so that it will hold your cup. I really like that I can use the kcup or use reg coffee in the basket. It\'s nice to be able to use it either way. Cleaning it is a breeze too.'),
(2599, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-03', 'Five Stars Superb product'),
(2600, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-24', 'Great product The blender works great. It is light and easy to carry. I have not yet used to travel cup but the blender is great.'),
(2601, 1, 1, 4, '2016-10-29', 'It\'s a good one.... I was skeptical about this model before I tried it, thinking the low tech model is easiest and reliable, and the latest and greatest model would have better features. But this one worked out beautifully. BEST features are the sleeker design and the strength control. (Over the low tech model, you also gain the carafe size and quieter process.) Things you\'ll MISS from the latest and greatest model are the Mug option and the ability to program the night before. (But the sleeker size is a gain.) My take on other review comments..... - I\'ve experienced no major dripping problem, but I wait for the screen to show it\'s finished before I grab the cup. - Yes there\'s condensation on the reservoir lid, and a colored top would be nice, but it\'s less visible in the back, therefore less bothersome to me. - No it\'s not lightning quick, but a little multitasking will prevent you from the urge to hover, then it\'s ready before you know it. - At first I was frustrated by how much water is required to brew a single cup, and that the screen won\'t move without adding some, but once I started filling the reservoir, it seemed less problematic. (I think more than a half liter remaining is required to move forward.) - I like knowing there\'s a workaround by using the  cover of a Keurig pod over a non Keurig pod, though there\'s plenty of inexpensive quality Keurig pods available. But even better is a reusable 2.0 pod with paper filters from BB&B. I\'ve easily used both reusable KCup and KCarafe pods before, to maximize flexibility and minimize cleanup and waste. - If you\'re going to use a carafe, I recommend the INSULATED one, based on experience with another model. Though this model does heat the water hotter for carafes than for cups, it\'s probably still a good investment. Overall, I\'ve been very happy to have this model on my counter. If you\'re serving a lot of people without a sink nearby, such as in an office environment, a model with a larger reservoir might be in order.'),
(2602, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-02', 'Toasts perfectly My brother said \"this toast works almost too perfect!\" Everything is evenly toasted. We love it and the s\'mores it makes.'),
(2603, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-18', 'Cuisinart great coffee maker! Very good product, this took the place of another Cuisinart that I had for 5yrs. Great coffee maker! Also love the light when pouring a cup!'),
(2604, 3, 1, 2, '2015-11-08', 'Short Power Cord The wire rack is flimsy. The power cord is so short that it won\'t reach past the edge of the toaster. If your outlet isn\'t immediately behind the toaster, you\'re going to have a bad time.'),
(2605, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-08', 'Great for the price Perfectly adequate toaster oven. Great for the price.'),
(2606, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Five Stars very happy.  thanks'),
(2607, 5, 1, 3, '2016-12-19', 'Love the removable tank Love the removable tank. Less mess than pouring from carafe into tank. The face plate over the buttons and LCD is cheap and falls off easily and you cannot interrupt a brew to pour a cup.'),
(2608, 10, 1, 1, '2015-09-28', 'Not great I\'ve had the blender about a month now and the motor already went out. I didn\'t use it everyday, not that that should be a factor. The warranty guarantees a year but I only got a month.'),
(2609, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-02', 'Not impressed at all. First the top leaks when ... Not impressed at all. First the top leaks when blending, second while drinking it leaks on the edges. Lit is on tight. . . Motor has a burnt smell that comes out of it while blending. . .I guess I got what I paid for. Utter junk.'),
(2610, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-01', 'Five Stars Perfect if you live alone or you\'re the only one who drinks coffee .'),
(2611, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-29', 'Five Stars Daughter loves it'),
(2612, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-07', 'I am pleased with how easy it is to use Works really well, I am pleased with how easy it is to use.'),
(2613, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'Five Stars great'),
(2614, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Best Keurig Yet! I\'ve loved Keurig from the start but they\'ve outdone themselves this time!  I haven\'t used all of the features so I can only let you know so much.  If you like your coffee strong, you\'re in luck.  There\'s a feature that makes the coffee brew stronger!  Also, it has a touchscreen which is always fun.  I\'ve had great coffee every morning since I got this.  You couldn\'t tear it out of my arms! (Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review).'),
(2615, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'Very good toaster! I haven\'t tried the bagel setting yet Very good toaster! I haven\'t tried the bagel setting yet, but for a poptart it works Very well! Start low.... I started at #4 heat and it got very toasted! #2 worked for me for a barely toasted, but nicely warmed.'),
(2616, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-15', 'Five Stars Works great, and a good price.'),
(2617, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-15', 'Durable toaster that does its job well This is a great, basic toaster that is built well for the job. It toasts evenly and just overall runs well. The toasting numbers may run on the lower end, meaning you can burn bread at a lower setting compared to other toasters- which isn\'t a problem, only something to learn as you use it.'),
(2618, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-03', 'Five Stars so far so good'),
(2619, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-03', 'I like it. The toaster is very compact and functional. I like it.'),
(2620, 2, 1, 3, '2015-12-04', 'Drawback -  toaster function requires you reset it from 0 each time - dial has very few marks - have to watch and stop by hand Accomodates large items, like bialys and toasts evenly. Major drawback is that the toaster function requires that you reset it from zero each time with a dial that has very coarse markings. So the machine cannot remember prior toast settings and there is little chance you can get the required doneness without continually watching it to catch it at the right time.'),
(2621, 4, 1, 1, '2016-09-13', 'so it was working fine until today Ok, so it was working fine until today.  It\'s no longer working.  Don\'t waste your money on this product - it lasted less than a year.'),
(2622, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I am obligated to say that I am receiving free pods to write this unbiased review for Keurig. I have been using my new Keurig 2.0 coffee maker for a little over 3 weeks now and overall I would say I am pretty impressed with it. Comparing to my old office pro it is much quieter and compact and certainly doesn\'t drip as much liquid or splash outside of the cup making it an easy clean up. Although I chose black, I also love the other color choices making it an easy gift for any occasion. The DRM sensor really doesn\'t bother me since I use all Keurig KCups anyway but I can see it being annoying for someone who likes coffee that isn\'t yet in KCups. I don\'t like that the maker doesn\'t have an auto shut off/turn on and that the lid on the back comes completely off every time you fill the water tank which also has a ton of condensation that builds up on the lid when you leave the coffee maker on all the time. I realize that if I was to get a higher model that these features would be on it but I think its something simple to even put on the lowest model. I would still highly recommend this model to anyone looking for a good reliable brewer.'),
(2623, 6, 1, 3, '2015-12-19', 'Three Stars Inconsistent heat transfer'),
(2624, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-18', 'Hamilton beach coffee pot. Very nice coffee pot , my Wife tells me that it is the best coffee pot that she has ever had. I think that she said it brews a pot of coffee in three minutes.'),
(2625, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-06', 'Five Stars Works great. Has enough power to toast bread quickly without drying it out.'),
(2626, 12, 1, 4, '2014-05-10', 'Great little toaster This is a great inexpensive toaster and toaster oven, needed a small functional toaster oven for my counter, this is great, sometimes heats things up too quick, so you need to keep an eye on things you heat up in the toaster oven.  Great color matches my kitchen perfectly.'),
(2627, 5, 1, 3, '2014-12-22', 'love the removable tank, glass caraffe lacks in design I am really liking my new coffeemaker, I\'ve been using it for a few weeks now. I love the removable tank! I am happy I will now be able to clean out my coffee maker so much easier.  Disappointed with the glass carafe. It is shaped in a way that if I am holding my cup in hand and pouring the last bit of the pot into the cup, hot coffee drips out the sides of the lid and onto my hand, ouch. That being said, I only had to do that once to realize that I just need to set the cup on the counter and wipe up any spillage.  The control features for brew \'bold\' and brew \'regular\' are ok I guess but not sure if it made that much difference in taste. The look of the maker is nice and compact, the clock is great, and I like the settings that reduce the temperature of the plate avoiding scorching. I give it 3 stars because of the poor shape of the carafe but over all I would still recommend this coffee pot for all it\'s other great features.'),
(2628, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-12', 'Five Stars Gets the job done in a jiffy!'),
(2629, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-28', 'Five Stars Excellent coffee maker.  Does not drip when pouring.  Would recommend.'),
(2630, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-07', 'Works Great! and well designed! This is an excellent coffee maker, also looked it up and no BPA You can pour it out without a spill very well designed.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(2631, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-04', 'What a great gift idea this was! I gifted this toaster oven to my sister because she was lighting her oven to make toast.  I knew it was compact enough to fit in her small kitchen but be efficient enough to meet her needs.  She was so grateful and loves using it.  She said it is a time saver for her and saves on her gas bill.'),
(2632, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Five Stars awesome item,,gave as a gift.'),
(2633, 8, 1, 1, '2016-10-14', 'Cool color but useless The even blue coloring was a cool effect,  but the lumen (light) output was a joke. At night,  there\'s so little light  output that from the driver seat, its like you don\'t even have your lights on. ** I would not recommend these bulbs for night driving **.'),
(2634, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-22', 'Great Price Works very fast and  heats things up quicker than an  oven'),
(2635, 7, 3, 1, '2015-10-30', 'The FlexBrew would spit coffee grounds out over the counter and in the cup. I try using it off and on to see if it was me. It would spit coffee all over every time I use it.'),
(2636, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-18', 'Five Stars Good quality!'),
(2637, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'GOOD STUFF NICE QUALITY'),
(2638, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-24', 'Great for different applications! After our old toaster bit the dust, I thought that this would be a good replacement. It was larger and looks like it can do more than just toast bread. I was right! I use this for all sorts of food and it makes it very easy for me to create \"baked\" meals in a small oven! Perfect!'),
(2639, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-14', 'Five Stars Great for price'),
(2640, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-05', 'but it looks great. Haven\'t used it yet, but it looks great.'),
(2641, 6, 1, 1, '2016-09-10', 'What a piece of garbage! Don\'t look for quality because of the name ... What a piece of garbage!  Don\'t look for quality because of the name (Cuisinart).  They (China) have removed all of the electrical/electronic controls, and what you have left is a manual toaster, e.i. a piece of garbage.  It\'s not enough that we\'ve lost the jobs (manufacturing) to China, but why are we left having to buy an inferior product ?.'),
(2642, 10, 1, 4, '2015-08-05', 'Works for now Not sure how long a life this will have. Good thing I don\'t use any ice in my shakes because I don\'t think this would have the power to break it up.'),
(2643, 5, 1, 2, '2016-09-15', 'I really really wanted to love this coffee maker I really really wanted to love this coffee maker. And I actually do except for 2 huge issues. First, something about the way this drips causes the grounds to overflow into our main pot. We never make more than 8 cups, and it still overflows. We\'ve tried the filter baskets and several thin brands of paper filters. Our old Mr Coffee never did this, and we haven\'t changed coffee brands, so I believe the finger points to this maker. Additionally, the plastic portion covering the digital read out and the buttons keeps popping off. It seems to get caught on the filter swing out holder. Perhaps just got a lemon.. but I\'m returning this after 2 weeks of giving it a fair shot.'),
(2644, 12, 1, 4, '2015-04-15', 'Nice appliance for the counter top! Great little toaster -- solved the argument at our household, \"oven vs. toaster.\"  It toasts perfectly and the mouth is wide enough for anything we\'ve put in so far (bagels fit great).  My only comment is that the over could have used just 1\" more in height, as what can fit in it is quite limited. For our purposes, however, we don\'t use the oven much.  Hopefully, it will last a long time.'),
(2645, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-15', 'Excellent buy Excellent buy'),
(2646, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-02', 'This is a product used to make in China, ... This is a product used to make in China, do not purchase. I bought it on Amazon and it burned itself after a couple of months. Here are the pics.'),
(2647, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-19', 'Five Stars LOVE it!! Never leaks and makes very good coffee! Can\'t beat it for the price!'),
(2648, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-30', 'Four Stars I AM HAPPY WITH THE OVEN ....'),
(2649, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-21', 'Five Stars Great replacement for the toaster oven that just broke. Got here pretty quick too.'),
(2650, 6, 1, 2, '2015-07-14', 'Two Stars DOES NOT TOAST ON BOTH SIDES'),
(2651, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-08', 'Awesome! This was a present for a very good friend of my beautiful daughter. She received it on her birthday, that was a plus..the Amazon prime shipping is the best, so very much reliable. My daughter friend love it, first because of the beautiful color, it match her color scheme perfectly. I was very pleased that the color was just picture by the seller and for quality, Keurig has proved how great their products are and I love the variety in product.. To be able to find such great variety of colors was awesome and surprising; you always see the generic color on the stores, so I was very happy to find the great variety and great price..thank you Amazon'),
(2652, 8, 1, 5, '2014-08-25', 'Five Stars Grate house gift'),
(2653, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-10', 'I love the retro classic look of this toaster I love the retro classic look of this toaster! The one I had for years finally blew two weeks ago, so while browsing for new toasters, I settled on this one. Some people posted that their toast was getting launched when it was done toasting. Thankfully, that doesn\'t happen with mine! Happy with my purchase!'),
(2654, 5, 1, 1, '2015-08-27', 'That blue light is painful to look at but I got used to it That blue light is painful to look at but I got used to it.  But only for a month, until the coffee maker just died.  It\'s like it\'s not plugged in...  I read the warranty and it looks like I am responsible for shipping back to the manufacturer. So that\'s $16 in shipping I have to incur due to a faulty product.  Do yourself a favor and spend a little more on a good quality brand.'),
(2655, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'Better Than Expected I wanted to get a cheap coffee maker without gimmicky features, but my wife didn\'t like the looks of them in the kitchen. Reading all the reviews on this unit, I was a little apprehensive buying this coffeemaker, especially since it was more expensive than the cheapies. But after having it for a couple months, I really like it.  I love that it swivels so I can pour the water into the back (or you could remove the separate semi-transparent filling container to fill at the sink).  I also like that you can adjust the temperature of the warming heater below the carafe (Low-Med-High settings).  I dislike old, burnt coffee from having too much heat  from the warming plate, and this is a good solution to reducing the \"baking\" while in the carafe, before I can turn the unit off. I usually only make 4 cups each morning.  There\'s a 3-4 cup setting that makes the brewing slower so it can distribute the water to all the grounds in the flat bottomed filter housing.  It makes really good, bold coffee while using a normal amount of coffee. Some people complain about the buttons.  I think they are fine, and don\'t see issue with them.  I like the coffee maker, and my wife likes the way it looks on the counter.  We\'re both happy!'),
(2656, 6, 1, 4, '2014-06-04', 'A good basic toaster No complaints.  It toasts pretty evenly, handles bagels, and is pretty fast.  The only reason I don\'t give it 5 stars is because it\'s just a toaster and I don\'t \"love it\".'),
(2657, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-31', '... oven for a little more than a month and love it. Better than heating my full size oven ... Have had this oven for a little more than a month and love it. Better than heating my full size oven up. i know I will love it even more in the summer months.'),
(2658, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-15', 'gives you the best of both worlds I think this is probably one of the most impressive Keurig models on the market today. I like that you have the option to make one cup or an entire pot, using the carafe. I did find it kind of annoying that the carafe had to be bought separately, and you were not able to use just any pot, but the ability to make either or, depending on your mood was nice. I find that the coffee brewed out of this Keurig tastes better than in previous Kuerigs I have owned. I\'m not sure if this is the brand of the coffee, or if this system has found a way to brew the coffee to the perfect temperature so as not to burn it. I think for the price, this is a good system to buy because it offers you the best of both worlds; single cup on the go, or multiple cups when entertaining. Although I did receive this product for free for testing, I would recommend buying it.'),
(2659, 12, 1, 1, '2015-08-09', 'Ignore the high-star reviews, they\'re all wrong It does a mediocre job at toasting and baking, there only enough room in the oven for a 10\" pizza if you cut it in half and put the halves in diagonally, and after two weeks the toaster broke.  This is not a good product.'),
(2660, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-15', 'Five Stars Its an awesome toaster!'),
(2661, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-21', 'Easy to use Easy to use, easy to clean, but a bit slow to brew.  I still gave it 5 stars as you have to favor in the low price as well.'),
(2662, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Five Stars Perfect size for me and it makes decent coffee.'),
(2663, 4, 1, 3, '2015-07-03', 'Broiler temp control? Text around the knobs is too small but I knew that before purchase.  The knobs have a raised ridge that serves as a pointer but it\'s impossible to see so I painted mine with some white paint and it\'s ok. Biggest disappointment is the broiler temp control.  There is none (that I can figure out).  It broils at max temp (>450degF) which is a bit aggressive.  I\'m not sure what to do about it.  Amazon is good on returns but packing the stuff is a huge PIA.'),
(2664, 4, 1, 1, '2016-06-27', 'Burnt toast I don\'t like this toaster oven by Cuisinart: 1. this toaster oven makes a loud bang as the metal cools. 2. Everything gets burnt on the toast setting--the bagels, the toast, rolls etc., even on the lightest setting. 3. When the timer goes off it makes a very loud beeping sound that goes on for a long time. 4. The tray that comes with it is cheap looking and too small for the size of the oven. It feels like a cheap knock-off of other Cuisinart toaster ovens. I had a Cuisinart toaster oven that I really liked, but it is no longer available. I really don\'t like it and would not recommend it. The only good thing about it is that the crumb tray opens from the front.'),
(2665, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-25', 'this one by far is the very best I have ever had I have had had several coffee makers over the years, this one by far is the very best I have ever had , several options , easy to put water in, most of all  YOU DONT SPILL ANY COFFEE WHEN YOU POUR IT.'),
(2666, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-30', 'Best ever! We received it promptly and in great shape. I have never had a better oven at ANY price.We hardly use the oven in the range amy more. Love it!!'),
(2667, 12, 1, 2, '2014-11-18', 'The toaster doesn\'t fit two slices of bread very easily if your loaf is wider than Wonder The toaster doesn\'t fit two slices of bread very easily if your loaf is wider than Wonder. For mine the slices overlap and the overlapping areas remain untoasted. It also has a habit of setting of my smoke alarm if I set the toaster at level 5 or higher. This is even after I clear out all the crumbs. The oven part is also pretty small and I couldn\'t put a hoagie in it without removing the top. Fun note: before I figured out I had to do this the top of the sandwich was touching a heating element and burned pretty badly. Pros: it was cheap...'),
(2668, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'I really love this oven! I really love this oven. I was able to toast and baked my dishes for my family without burning it. This is such a perfect one for me.'),
(2669, 6, 1, 4, '2016-05-02', 'Four Stars Shade choices are good.  Easy to clean.  Fair price.'),
(2670, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-30', 'From 2006 forward...Great performance! I bought this item, as a gift for a fisherman. He is happy with it, so I bought on for self. I\'m still using an older Model, going on seven years now. I just wanted this; Just In Case. Cuisinart produces fine appliances.'),
(2671, 8, 1, 4, '2015-08-04', 'Four Stars Good size for my 86 year old mother. She says it makes good coffee and it stays hot.'),
(2672, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-26', 'Good Great for the price.  Works as expected.'),
(2673, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-17', 'Five Stars Works great.  no problems.  easy to use.  Arrived on time.'),
(2674, 5, 1, 1, '2016-10-13', 'First one was great.  Then 3 died of the same problem....Avoid Had one of these for about 2 years with absolutely no complaints.  Worked great.  Around that 2 year point it stopped working.  Tinkering with it suggested that lack of cleaning had allowed debilitating calcium build up - my fault.  No big deal, two years was a decent life. Ordered a new one from Amazon.  Within two weeks the silver cover over the buttons fell off.  The plastic posts holding it on (screws come in from the back/interior) disintegrated and broke.  Figured it was a fluke and sent it back to Amazon for a replacement.  Replacement did the same thing in the same timeframe.  Bad batch?  Sent the replacement back for replacement.  Same thing happened in just over a month Unfortunately, this put it outside of the Amazon replacement time limit.  Contacted HB directly.  After several emails and sending copies of receipts they responded with their warranty coverage option.  They said normally, I would have to send them the bad unit (about $12 of shipping) but they would accept a photo of the cord having been cut off.  (as if I could not fix that if I were trying to scam them)  Then within 2 weeks they would ship another unit back to me.  BUT...I would need to pay for that shipping.  So I would have to call to pay for that with a CC. Sooo, their idea of extra special CS on a problem that happened 3 times and is obviously a systemic or production flaw was for me to be without a coffee maker for 2 to 3 weeks and to pay a third of the cost of the unit.  All of that to get a unit that experience suggests will last about a month.  To be fair, the unit still made coffee without the trim plate, but what else might break?  and has inner parts exposed did not seem to be a good idea. Despite our initial positive experience with this brand and model, the evidence suggests that their quailty/quality control/manufacturing/materials have declined to unacceptable levels.  Despite their economically questionable \"exceptional CS\" offer, we will try our luck with a different brand and model. Buy at your own risk.'),
(2675, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-23', 'It also is very effective for many other things like making tater tots or to heat up a sandwich ... It makes toast very well, which can\'t be said of all toaster ovens surprisingly. It also is very effective for many other things like making tater tots or to heat up a sandwich and melt cheese.'),
(2676, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-09', 'Five Stars Excellent product, we love it...and the great shipping service with Prime takes the cake.'),
(2677, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-06', 'A great product I love my new Keurig! It was definitely time for an upgrade. I love the color too!.'),
(2678, 5, 1, 3, '2016-01-28', 'Good taste but SLOW Love the feature to select temperature and boldness. Takes very long to brew - 15 min.'),
(2679, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Nice looking toaster, works great! I bought this after another manufacturer\'s inexpensive toaster simply stopped heating. Out of the blue- after just a few months! So far so good with this one, though too soon to say how long it will last. I will update if it dies prematurely. It is very nice looking and the three knobs are pretty straightforward. Not too big, not too small. It has already been used for toast and appetizers and it works perfectly. Very happy to have a  functional toaster again, and a fine looking one at that! I am optimistic it will last.'),
(2680, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Love the colors available Love the colors available. But most of all I can have a fresh cup of coffee anytime I want.  Key word is fresh.  I don\'t like coffee that\'s sits for any length of time. Love my new machine. I had the mini Keurig before.  Everyone can have a different flavor without making a whole pot. Love IT!!'),
(2681, 5, 1, 4, '2014-09-13', 'Four Stars Very happy with the way the coffee maker works only complaint is washing out carafe due to cover.'),
(2682, 10, 1, 4, '2015-05-28', 'Nice little personal blender! :) For the size of this blender, it really is a cute little powerhouse of a device!  However there is just one little thing that is frustrating.  When you are adding large chunks of frozen fruit it does get stuck a little bit.  So I\'d suggest waiting until your fruit are a little thawed.  BUT works best with fresh fruits.  I really do enjoy it!'),
(2683, 5, 1, 4, '2016-01-16', 'Easy to use and makes a great cup Solid Coffee Maker. Easy to use and makes a great cup!'),
(2684, 8, 1, 2, '2015-08-17', 'Two Stars Decanter spills every time you pour.'),
(2685, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-18', 'Great Value Awesome value and works perfectly. I would definitely recommend, especially at for the price.'),
(2686, 8, 1, 3, '2016-10-29', 'Product is perfect for camping Product is perfect for camping, beach house or secondary home, which it why I purchased.  Works great for occasional use, due to so much thinner plastic, which changes shape a little to close the top lid, where you dump the coffee. You get what you pay for.'),
(2687, 9, 1, 2, '2016-01-22', 'Two Stars I am very upset with this coffe maker. My coffee comes out luke warm'),
(2688, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'Five Stars works well and fits in center of car holder and simple rinse with hot water'),
(2689, 6, 1, 5, '2014-03-09', 'Cuisnart Toaster Very pleased with my purchase.  Easy settings, wide slots and looks nice sitting on my counter.  Would highly recommend this toaster!'),
(2690, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-20', 'Portable yet powerful Small, compact, and powerful enough to mix my morning smoothie.  I was looking for something that was portable to take to work and this fits the bill.  Liked it so much I bought one for home as well.  Highly recommend'),
(2691, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', 'Buy It Really like this coffee maker. The best part for me is the side water unit. Easy to read, so filling it accurately is a breeze. Consistently great coffee. Spouse loves the light spotlighting the cup while dispensing in the early am before work.'),
(2692, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-26', 'Five Stars Makes good toast and is a very attractive  appliance. Meets expectations.'),
(2693, 6, 1, 5, '2016-04-11', 'Good toaster, great price, prompt shipping. Still working great after 6 months or so and used every day. Consistent settings. Why spend a lot when this does the job well?'),
(2694, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-07', 'oven great toaster not so great Is a nice little oven but the toaster is hard to set and you have to watch it closely because ut burns quickly.  You cant set the toaster on a set setting so each time it can be slightly different.  But it makes great snacks bagel bites etc.'),
(2695, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-30', 'It\'s a toaster Best toaster we ever owned. Toasts quickly and larger slots are great for bagels.'),
(2696, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-26', 'This is not the toaster oven you are looking for. Cannot make toast to save its life.  This model has a mechanical timer, and the difference between \"not toasted\" and \"burnt\" is so microscopic that it is completely useless as a toaster.  I bought it to replace an old Black & Decker that looked similar & worked fine for many years, but the new one is utter crap.  Don\'t buy it.'),
(2697, 8, 1, 5, '2015-11-11', 'Great coffee maker We put this in our 1 bedroom rental at the NJ shore perfect size for 2-3 people'),
(2698, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-15', 'We bought this to replace the same one we\'d had ... We bought this to replace the same one we\'d had for 6 years  Unfortunately the new one does not toast evenly and doesn\'t work well.'),
(2699, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'Five Stars Easy to clean and fill.  Makes great tasting coffee.'),
(2700, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-12', 'Five Stars works good easy to use'),
(2701, 9, 1, 4, '2016-01-31', 'Four Stars GOOD PRODUCT'),
(2702, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-22', 'I purchased this from the store and when I got it home was going to run a couple of cups of water thru it to clean it. When I ran one cup thru the bold cycle worked fine. I then ran a cup of cold water thru the regular cycle and it would not pump the water out of the reservoir. The motor would run like it was trying to pump but it would not actually pump it out. I unplugged the unit and then dumped it out, difficulty, and then tried it again with new cold water. Still would not pump the water out. No K-cup, no filter, and no grounds to clog anything the entire time. It will be going back to the store ASAP.'),
(2703, 9, 1, 3, '2015-11-03', 'The coffee reservoir leaks, when you called support, ... The coffee reservoir leaks, when you called support, all I got was a song and dance, B.S. instead of standing by their product, ALL I want is buy another reservoir, I still can\'t get one.'),
(2704, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-01', 'Excellent design, and very smart features. In the world of coffee makers, this is easily the best choice. You get a fluid gauge just like fuel in a vehicle, a smart timing system that is fairly intuitive, visible water level in a modular water reservoir (this was a great time saver for me), and a wide push down lever for filling the cup for lazy or arthritic hands. The clock light is not obnoxious either, just a very smooth bluish tint. Let\'s not forget a light for the filling area as well. This is all offered in a fairly space conscious design. The filter system for the water is more of a suggestion, but I already fill from a filtered water container to begin with. I\'m not sponsored by these guys or anything, this is just the best coffee maker i\'ve purchased to date and i\'m quite happy with it! I am quite happy and would definitely recommend this product.'),
(2705, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Love Hamilton Personal  Blender! Easy to use, very portable, personal blender. Cord wraps around base. Easy clean-up. Makes effort toward eating/drinking healthier  much easier..at least for me. Love it.'),
(2706, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-13', 'I love it! It is in perfect condition when I opened it. It will definitely be convenient for rush hour, break time at work, and such. I recommend pressing the pulse 2-3 seconds repeatedly if needed. But, not more than 10 times. Also, I don\'t recommend blending oranges and soy milk together because that was the first two ingredients I used today. It tasted too creamy and the two combinations didn\'t work out for me.. Bleh. The blender was easy to clean as well. Overall, I love this blender because it doesn\'t take too much space and it is easy to use.'),
(2707, 8, 1, 5, '2014-09-26', 'Perfect 5 cup coffee maker I had previously purchased a black version of this maker.  It worked so well I purchased this white B&D 5 cup drip coffee maker.  Now I make regular coffee in the black one and decaf in the white one.  No body in the house is confused which is the decaf.  LOL.  The coffee maker is easy to use.  You may need to make a couple of batches of coffee until you determine the quantity of coffee grounds for your preferred cup of java.'),
(2708, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-14', 'Four Stars great  toaster'),
(2709, 4, 1, 1, '2016-12-09', 'Not great Everything was either under cooked or burnt, no in between.'),
(2710, 6, 1, 1, '2016-02-21', 'Returning it. Think it\'s defective. Toasts one side ... Returning it.  Think it\'s defective.  Toasts one side much more than other  and have to turn up very high to toast.'),
(2711, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-29', 'Works great. It\'s a toaster Works great.  It\'s a toaster.  Used it to toast bagels, frozen waffles and sliced bread.  I don\'t know what else you can say about a toaster...'),
(2712, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Good oven and toaster This toaster toasts well and the oven part works like a charm.  Love it.  The only drawback is that it needs to stay four inches from any back or side wall and it is not small so it take up some space.  But I had the space and it met all my requirements.'),
(2713, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-16', 'Love This!!! All the positive review are right on.  We leave it on our counter and use it every day.  The oven is absolutely a Perfect size for most every day needs.  We had a larger one years ago that was just too big.  We got the red, and it dresses up our kitchen.  My favorite item so far in the year.'),
(2714, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'Five Stars great product, bought as a gift.'),
(2715, 7, 3, 4, '2015-05-11', 'I was very excited to try the Hamilton Beach Flex Brew coffee maker. According to the package you can use the k-cups or regular ground up coffee, which is a nice feature. We first used it with the k-cups, and it worked just fine. The amount of water you add is the amount of coffee that comes out, so pretty fool proof. We then tried it with just regular ground up coffee, and unfortunately there was some grounds that got in the cup of coffee. It is possible that the coffee was too finely ground, and that was the issue - as we do grind our own coffee beans. I have not tried it with regular coffee that you purchase ground already, as I said, this may make the difference. Or perhaps the little round coffee packets already in the filter would work better. Over all, I am very happy with this product. It has a nice slim design, so it should fit easily on your counter. It brews very quickly, and you can control how weak of strong you want your coffee by the amount of water you put in. I definitely recommend this Hamilton Beach coffee maker.'),
(2716, 7, 3, 4, '2015-12-19', 'Product is o.k. for the price. Generic coffee pods which we tried did not work in this coffee maker. Next time we would probably try a higher priced version for higher quality.'),
(2717, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-25', 'This is my second pot like this. I absolutely love this Coffee Maker This is my second pot like this.  I absolutely love this Coffee Maker!!.'),
(2718, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-18', 'Nice coffee maker This puppy works the way a coffee maker should.  Now we wait to see if it has the staying power to outlast our previous units.  It is really easy to get water into this unit without spilling,  Lots of nice design features missing in many more expensive units.'),
(2719, 8, 1, 4, '2016-09-29', 'It\'s like a personal coffee maker It\'s like a personal coffee maker. There isn\'t enough for me and my roommate but I like to drink big cups.'),
(2720, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-07', 'Overenthusiastic Can be a bit overenthusiastic in comparison to my last toaster oven. Keep an eye on what you cook in it so it doesn\'t burn!'),
(2721, 9, 1, 5, '2015-07-19', 'Five Stars Best coffee pot around. My coffee is delicious!'),
(2722, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-03', 'Terrific product. Works great!.'),
(2723, 2, 1, 1, '2016-05-18', 'One Star Bread failed to toast.  I returned it.'),
(2724, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-13', 'great little oven ! very satisfied it does everything we want it to do'),
(2725, 1, 1, 2, '2016-09-05', 'So this product is not as good as the older models I bought this to replace an older unit.  I am so sorry that i did.  It is very fragile, I have lost a large number of pods because the coffee grinds found their way into the coffee cup.  Today I got an error on the display screen asking me to call Keurig for help.  I did, and after 45 minutes on the phone with Keurig support, a replacement machine has been ordered.  Then I received a coupon from Keurig in an e-mail saying \"order pods\" - I brought up Keurig\'s website, selected the pods i wanted entered the coupon code and received \"0.00\" discount.  So this product is not as good as the older models, does not have a timeout feature and has cost me dozens of pods.  Would not by this model again - ever.'),
(2726, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-06', 'Four Stars Not the best blender, weak on ice or frozen fruit, but good value for the price.'),
(2727, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-13', 'Five Stars We love it, it\'s perfect'),
(2728, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'Very Nice unit. Works well and has lots of features Very Nice unit.  Works well and has lots of features.  Can set it and forget it when making toast or bagels in the morning.'),
(2729, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-14', 'Four Stars What can I say.... it\'s a toaster, it toasts stuff.'),
(2730, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'Reasonably Price Efficient Toaster We are big fans of this little toaster oven since we started using it about a month ago. It has a sleek design and toasts things QUICKLY! Much faster than the slightly bigger Black + Decker toaster oven that we were replacing. I would guess that it toasts as quickly as a regular toaster. The other features (bake, keep warm, broil) are great ass well. It seems to clean up easily, which I appreciate it. I would definitely buy it again, especially since it\'s so reasonably priced'),
(2731, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-05', 'Very easy to use Just bought this for my parents.  Very easy to use, cooks food quickly and evenly.'),
(2732, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-13', 'Is it bad that I consider a 5-cup pot a single-serving? I might have a problem... Seriously though, this thing makes good, hot coffee--that\'s it. Simple to use, lasts forever. It\'s perfect for someone who doesn\'t need a big fancy coffeemaker. Don\'t let the cheap price scare you. We\'ve had ours for at least 5 years and it\'s still going strong. Bought this second one for my grandmother after her larger coffeemaker died.'),
(2733, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-16', 'Best coffee maker! I bought this after getting rid of my Keurig and I absolutely love it! I love that I can fill up the separate water container so I don\'t have to worry about spilling. I can also choose temperature and how strong the coffee is. Love it!'),
(2734, 4, 1, 3, '2016-04-23', 'I really liked this oven and it worked really great but only ... I really liked this oven and it worked really great but only lasted about two years.  A part of the heating coil split open a little after a year (probably should have throw it out at that point for safety reasons) but I continued to use it...lasted another year before it made a big spark one day and I threw it out.'),
(2735, 2, 1, 4, '2015-09-30', 'Real nice oven. Helps a lot and I use it ... Real nice oven. Helps a lot and I use it to make sandwiches and it toasts them perfectly. Only thing to watch out for is if you heat foods that contain something that would melt ( like cheese) then use the tray they provide that goes under the metal. It prevents the spillage from reaching the heating rods. Overall great product for the price. No one could belive I got this for $25'),
(2736, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-28', 'crunchy AND crisp every single time with this product Do you want to achieved that perfect crunch and crisp of food that your cooking then you need to check this Stainless Steel 7-Quart Oval Manual Slow Cooker just made for you.'),
(2737, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-12', 'Five Stars best coffee maker we\'ve ever had. Keeps it at just the right temp, and easy to fill a cup.'),
(2738, 6, 1, 4, '2015-01-15', 'Much better toaster than the majority on the market Much better toaster than the majority on the market...not as good as the old toaster from years ago..they were much better back then.'),
(2739, 9, 1, 2, '2016-07-20', 'Two Stars Sent back'),
(2740, 6, 1, 2, '2015-12-01', 'Ok unit, but broke after a year of light usage I bought this model 14 months ago. It broke after a year of light usage. Called Cuisinart, rep demanded that we mail in the broken unit. They were not willing to send a box or a return label (interestingly, only residents of California can receive them, according to the rep). Prior to being defective it worked fine, though breadcrumbs and pieces of bread easily get caught and burn.'),
(2741, 4, 1, 4, '2015-04-10', 'Put away your toaster, don\'t heat the big oven After receiviing this toaster oven as a gift a couple years ago,  I recently purchased one for my son and wife for their anniversary.  We bake frozen pizzas in it, plus tater tots and French fries, etc.. besides making toast, bagles, of course.  I\'m giving it 4 stars because it doesn\'t have a timer in the baking cycle.  It does a great job.'),
(2742, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-18', 'Five Stars Nice little toaster.  Perfect for the price.'),
(2743, 3, 1, 4, '2016-07-10', 'LCD is not backlight, but a solid product. I\'ve had it for a few months now, and it works well.  Took off one star because the LCD panel is not backlight as it is in the graphic.  It\'s hard to read the LCD, and the labels on the buttons are also hard to see.'),
(2744, 7, 3, 4, '2014-10-21', 'So far I love it. No complaints.'),
(2745, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-16', 'The family loved it and says it works perfectly This was a gift.  The family loved it and says it works perfectly.  They said shipping was awesome and packaging as well.'),
(2746, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-23', 'where has this been all my life this is like my right hand on a lonely night. The only thing I need. Microwave is now obsolete, frozen foods are a go.'),
(2747, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-14', 'I feel spoiled. I use it all the time. Especially when heating bread items. I love it!'),
(2748, 11, 1, 1, '2014-01-13', 'WARNING! Defective Timer - Caused FIRE! The timer did not work and kept the toaster running until a piece of bread caught on FIRE!  Amazon promptly refunded money but this could have been terrible if I hadn\'t been able to quickly put the burning bread into the sink and douse it.'),
(2749, 5, 1, 4, '2014-04-16', 'Slow but otherwise great. The coffee comes out great. However, it is much slower than other coffee makers. The removable water container is great if you can use it. We fill it with filtered water from the fridge so it doesn\'t fit. But, it would be a great feature if just filling from the sink.'),
(2750, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-07', 'Five Stars So far so good'),
(2751, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'makes a very nice cup of coffee makes a very nice cup of coffee. Fast brew time at about 7 min. for 10 cups. shipping was fast.'),
(2752, 8, 1, 4, '2014-12-25', 'This was the perfect option for her to have her blend My wife only drinks decaf coffee. This was the perfect option for her to have her blend, and me to be able to brew my regular blend in our 12 cup coffee maker.'),
(2753, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-14', 'Cute, trendy, and awesome! If you are looking for a Keurig with great color choices, that takes up little space on your counter, then this is a great one!  My previous Keurig, which quit working after 2 years, was a full sized Keurig and I loved it. I live in an apartment and I have a small kitchen, so when I saw this smaller Keurig, I purchased it. This Keurig has a touch screen that gives you the option or 4, 6, 8 or 10 ounce cup choices.  On top of that, you can press the \"strong\" button and it will make your coffee considerably stronger.  This is nice, because there are times where I would like to fill my travel mug with 10 ounces, but I don\'t want to lose the flavor. The manual explains how to clean this Keurig.  None of the parts are dishwasher safe.  It also won\'t take non-Keurig brand cups.  I love Keurig, but I think that was a nasty move.  I truly hope that someone comes along and makes a better product that does take K-cups, and hurts Keurig financially because of it. This machine is louder then my old one, and it sounds funny when it brews.  It is hard to explain the sound, but it\'s an odd sound.  It\'s like it pulses.  You can\'t set this one to brew automatically, and it doesn\'t have a clock on it.  I don\'t care about either of those things, as I never used those features on my old Keurig, but if that is a problem for you, then you will need to find a different coffee maker. I bought the turquoise one, and it looks so trendy in my kitchen.  It is more green then blue, however, so keep that in mind if you are wanting to purchase the turquoise one. So far I love my new coffeemaker!  Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(2754, 6, 1, 4, '2016-08-21', 'Better than Costco toaster, but not perfect. We are giving a four because when you set the number to get a certain doneness to the toast...the results do not match up.  It pops up and you have to reset it again.  That is our minor problem, but toasts evenly, no burn spots like our last toaster we got at Costco.'),
(2755, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-25', 'Smoothie maker Great!  Perfect for just one person, or maybe two.'),
(2756, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-16', 'Five Stars This was a gift for my Granddaughter who just moved into her  apartment'),
(2757, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-20', 'good This was a smart purchase. Very efficient heat and cooks everything to perfection.A lot of room for a csserole or whole chicken. The Toaster also works great. Two thumbs up.'),
(2758, 12, 1, 4, '2014-12-05', 'Four Stars More small that I think but it works excellent. And is very nice.'),
(2759, 6, 1, 3, '2014-04-13', 'best bet, but button bucks This has everything a good toaster should have... many selections, a pop-up to retrieve lever, a dinger when done.  However, mine holds toast only on the left side, it seems, which is normal for some toasters.  But I really have to hit the button down hard for it to stay.  Makes perfect toast every time.'),
(2760, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-19', 'Five Stars Good product.'),
(2761, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-30', 'Works fine. The bottom knob is hard to turn to ... Works fine.  The bottom knob is hard to turn to the off position but it doesn\'t hurt to just let the timer run out.  Heats up fast.  Like any toaster oven you might want to do a preheat so the elements to burn your food up too fast.'),
(2762, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-11', 'I bought this to replace a Cuisinart Model ss-700. I was constantly having problems with the Cuisinart getting air in the lines and not working. I also had trouble with the filter inside the water chamber growing mold on it. I found the Hamilton Beach Flex Brew on walmart.com and decided to give it a try. I not only loved the price and small size, but also loved the fact that I can use either keurig k-cups or my regular coffee and it only holds enough water for 1 cup at a time. I have used it several times and so far don\'t have any complaints.'),
(2763, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-12', 'A must have kitchen appliance Let me start with this is my first convection oven or toaster oven and I was a bit skeptical on how well this would work, I was very surprised and impressed to say the least. I bought this for my wife as a gift and i am sure glad I did because this thing saves a lot of time cooking vs my oven and it also preheats faster. First and foremost this thing saves me money because of its size and its efficiency and the convection setting crisps food so good. It fits on my counter top without looking to big and it sure is nice looking and the digital display is very nice too. I have stopped using my microwave for a lot of things because of this, as well as my oven except for very large roasts. For the price I would say you will not find a more useful kitchen appliance or a better looking one.'),
(2764, 11, 1, 2, '2015-08-18', 'The oven is horrible. I put a small casserole in at 450 ... Glorified toaster. The oven is horrible. I put a small casserole in at 450 for an hour and the middle was still cold. It toasts o.k. and broils just alright but as an oven it doesn\'t work well at all. Very disappointed. Using an older toaster oven now instead.'),
(2765, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-23', 'Good if your not buying primarily to tosdt. I like it. Great price. Works fine for what I need it for. Burnt some toast here and there but i didn\'t buy it for toAst.'),
(2766, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-31', 'Five Stars yes Love it'),
(2767, 4, 1, 1, '2016-02-16', 'Fire Hazard - Not worth it. For the second time, after just over 3 years of use, the switch failed and the top elements do not shut off.  I loved it when it worked and thought the first failure was a fluke.  But now that the same thing happened on the replacement unit, it\'s a clear design flaw.  Thank God we were home when we realized it had never shut off and the exterior started smoking from the exessive heat.  Toast is nice, but not at the risk of a kitchen fire.'),
(2768, 9, 1, 4, '2016-08-06', 'We recommend it. We first saw this coffee maker in a resort we stayed in in Las Vegas.  Wouldn\'t you know it, within a few weeks our old coffee maker started leaking.  We bought this knowing how it worked.  I\'m giving this 4 out of 5 stars for two reasons.  First, the tank gauge is a little sticky, just like some of the other reviews have stated.  If you tap the top of the machine the needle will reset to show the amount of coffee remaining.  On the other hand, I never knew how much coffee was left in our old carafe so it\'s no big deal to me.  The second reason is the tank takes a little effort to clean.  However, the temperature at which the tank keeps the coffee and the ease of pouring a cup (the LED light showing how much is in your cup) are worth the effort.'),
(2769, 4, 1, 4, '2016-12-27', 'Toasts and bakes very consistently. The shrill beeper always ... Toasts and bakes very consistently.  The shrill beeper always makes me jump out of my skin, so I try to get to the toast before it goes off.  If you know it beeps only 5 times, you\'ll get used to it being over soon enough.  Crispy toast is worth it.'),
(2770, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-14', 'Awesome toaster I have never used a toaster oven before. I bought this to replace a toaster that my wife wanted to bury with me. Not happening. She says that will never work as good as our 30 year old mechanical marvel. Guess what my family loves this toaster. We use it everyday and enjoy it. The smallness of it works great for next to the fridge. Just be careful not to melt your cell phone charger cord on it. Thank you for the great toaster at a sweet price.'),
(2771, 12, 1, 1, '2016-01-14', 'One Star Awful had it for a couple of months and then had to purchase new one'),
(2772, 4, 1, 5, '2015-08-14', 'Loving it Really love how easy to use it is and how versatile it is. And it doesn\'t occupy a lot of space. Plus its way more \'precise\' than my other big oven (I can never tell what actual temperature that one is at and how fast or how slow it will heat up ). I have used this toaster oven to - make quiche, fruit pies, cakes, muffins, toast bread, bake chicken and fish, etc and it has worked easily, and fairly accurately every time. I really have no complaints about this one. I have been using this for >1 year now.'),
(2773, 5, 1, 1, '2015-12-12', 'Get the warranty Hasn\'t even been a year yet and it is already broken. Very unhappy with this purchase'),
(2774, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-29', 'Very Happy! Excellent product; I did my homework before I purchased, since my other percolator type coffee pot only lasted a short time.  Owned mine for about 6 months now, without any issues.  I especially like that the water reservoir can be detached and filled that way; great feature.  Looks good, too.'),
(2775, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-17', 'Simple to use, makes a good cup of Joe. Excellent single serving coffee brewer, with either K-cups or regular ground coffee.'),
(2776, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-05', 'Five Stars Great product at a great price'),
(2777, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-07', 'use it every day but it shuts off all the ... use it every day but it shuts off all the time and I\'m not done with it change it to 4 hour shut off.'),
(2778, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Excellent toaster Really a nice toaster.  Seems to make toast much faster than our more expensive last toaster. I\'d buy it again.'),
(2779, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-05', 'Five Stars The best coffee pot i ever had.'),
(2780, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-21', 'Should have bought one long ago. Excellent, well made appliance. Perfect size for me. Easy to use - two dials, temperature and time. No electronics to worry about, no flashing lights, etc. Loud \"DING\" when completed. Easy to clean. I wish the power cord was about one foot longer but I can live with this one. Yes, it does get hot but so does an oven and this doesn\'t take ages to warm up!'),
(2781, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'You need this I use this toaster oven EVERY.SINGLE.DAY. My first one lasted 5-6 years, the second one lasted about 4-5 years. I like everything about this model, so I ordered a back up (before it\'s gone forever). The convection is my favorite part. It heats quickly and evenly.'),
(2782, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'Top of the line and attractive Toaster Oven for a great price. Bought this for my elderly Mom to use.  She loves it and is perfect to fix healthy small meals in.  You can even bake as well as broil and toast in the oven.  Great deal.'),
(2783, 7, 3, 4, '2015-02-16', 'I was skeptical before I bought it, thinking it would be difficult. I was amazed how simple it is to brew a single cup of coffee....in the morning I have it all set up the night before, just have to hit the power button, less then 5 minutes later my cup of coffee is ready and I\'m out the door!'),
(2784, 2, 1, 2, '2016-09-04', 'white smoke that smelled like I was inhaling cancer So when I first turned it on it started smoking this opaque, white smoke that smelled like I was inhaling cancer. I immediately turned it off and unplugged it, and then took a closer look at the instructions. In the instructions it said that a little smoke upon first turning it on was \"normal\", which is pretty crazy.. But then when I turned it on again, something caught on fire inside! Something burnt dripped down onto my little mini pizza I was making. Again, I turned it off and unplugged it. Finally it started working normally. However, it cooks everything unevenly! In order to get an even cook I will have to stop halfway through and turn it around. If I don\'t, either one side will be cooked and the other burnt or one side will be undercooked and the other normal. I would not recommend this product.'),
(2785, 5, 1, 3, '2015-05-11', 'nice little coffee maker too Died with no warning after 6 months, nice little coffee maker too.'),
(2786, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Best decision ever! We just purchased the Keurig 2.0 brewing system and we love it! We are always on the the go and this has really helped get our coffee/tea fix in without wasting a whole lot of coffee!! We love our Keurig and all the different varieties we can choose from! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2787, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-04', 'Works for us! Makes fast.  Doesn\'t dribble when you pour.  So good so far.'),
(2788, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-08', 'Sleek looking This coffee machine is sleek, easy to clean, and rotates!'),
(2789, 11, 1, 5, '2014-05-30', 'I turned it on and it made me yummy garlic bread $10 a day going out to eat for lunch adds up fast. I bought this so I could make stuff at work. Between this and a Waring 1300watt hot plate. Now I can have yummy pasta and garlic bread at work and I only spend $2 instead of $10.'),
(2790, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-17', 'Hot coffee awesome features Love the front load for coffe grounds and the swivel to put water in the decanter in the rear why hasn\'t anyone figured this out before ?!'),
(2791, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-09', 'Coffee when you want it Simple one-button operation made for people who want coffee NOW and don\'t want to fuss with setting timers or clocks.  Add coffee grinds, add water, plug-in and push button = coffee.  Easy to clean and personal sized.'),
(2792, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-13', 'One Star It broke after one use'),
(2793, 1, 1, 4, '2015-09-09', 'Four Stars Love the color. Plan to really enjoy it during colder weather. It\'s 100 degrees out now!'),
(2794, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-30', 'Works great. love all the options Works great.  love all the options!  Looks great on the cabinet.'),
(2795, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-11', 'but we like this model Have one already.  Don\'t have delivery on the second one, but we like this model.  Using them in two homes'),
(2796, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-17', 'Great value for the money! Couldn\'t be happier with this machine. We replaced an aged Mr. Coffee machine that went kaput. I was weary about the Hamilton Beach name as it isn\'t a brand that I\'ve ever associated with quality. I\'m happy with the quality and features and it makes as good of a cup of coffee as anything in $50 of its price.'),
(2797, 10, 1, 1, '2016-01-16', 'Made for taking smoothies outside, yet no replacement parts offered. DO NOT BUY Didn\'t buy, don\'t have to. Soon as I see they don\'t offer replacement jars, lids etc you know it\'s crap.'),
(2798, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-13', '... few of these for our hotel and the Guests\' LOVE them! I\'ve even told them where to buy ... Bought a few of these for our hotel and the Guests\' LOVE them!  I\'ve even told them where to buy them!'),
(2799, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-22', 'Five Stars This has been a great space saver in my little kitchen.  Works very well!'),
(2800, 5, 1, 5, '2014-05-08', 'Hot, fast and easy! Great value for the money. It makes coffee hotter (and therefore, tastier) than any other drip machine I\'ve used. I LOVE the auto shut off because I don\'t have to worry after I\'ve left the house. Programming for start time is easy. Mostly, I LOVE the removable water reservoir and that\'s the primary reason I bought it. It is very easy to wash out the reservoir if a bug has gotten in there. It is almost impossible to wash out the water reservoir on the other style of drip machines. No complaints after two months of use, and I\'m planning to buy another to keep in the closet for the sad day when this one dies.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(2801, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Happy Keurig 2.0 Brew System Customer Have used my new Keurig 2.0 for a week now & am very pleased with it.  I had the smaller mini and wanted to transfer that one to our camper.  The 2.0 is slighltly larger than the mini but fits easily into the same space and has the advantage of onboard water storage which allows brewing multiple cups without re- filling each time.  Also can be used to brew a 4 cup carafe.  Also like the water filter feature & the two free filters that were provided.  Brews the same great cup of coffee!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods provided for this review!'),
(2802, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Great Machine Love this machine, hot coffee, like that I don\'t have to pour the water from the pot to the coffee make.'),
(2803, 12, 1, 4, '2017-01-04', 'DOES WHAT I NEED, Does what I need it to do.  I have one ding against it.  I like frozen waffles and they won\'t go in the top because they crumple and fall thru partially into the bottom.'),
(2804, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-23', 'Replacing Starbucks I have had this for a few day, so far so good. It is replacing my Starbucks Verismo brewer because those pods are getting expensive. I bought the espresso Keurig pods and brew the night before, refrigerate and use for iced machiattos the next morning.  You can select up to 10oz coffee with the regular pods. Just make sure you get 2.0 pods. it\'s easy to use and not too noisy.  This one has a filter, which I haven\'t used in a keurig before-I have an older one at my office. But you soak in water for 5 min and rinse for 1 and you\'re good for 6 months. I can\'t tell the difference using it and not ( I brewed the first cup without it).'),
(2805, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-14', 'Very nice unit Makes good coffee, really like the detachable water container, simple to use, Can\'t even come up with an improvement idea!'),
(2806, 5, 1, 2, '2015-05-28', 'We\'ve enjoyed this coffee maker We\'ve enjoyed this coffee maker, BUT we purchased this item on September 8, 2014, and it just broke this morning, May 28, 2015.. Might be me, but I feel like it should last longer than that.'),
(2807, 8, 1, 4, '2016-02-02', 'Coffee\'s tasty and the price is right The perfect little coffee pot for a small space. At $15 or so, it\'s a bargain (I\'m on my second after the first died after two years of regular use): it drips a perfectly tasty cup of coffee.'),
(2808, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-19', 'Good buy I love it. I saw it in our department first. Then when I moved in to my new apartment, I bought this immediately within my first week of move. A great thing to have. My friend also bought this after me. He even cooks chicken in there.'),
(2809, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'This is a great little travel blender This is a great little travel blender!!  Works well for meds as well as healthy meal drinks.  I love  this compact little blender. Stores in a fairly small area.  Great Buy!'),
(2810, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'Five Stars love it, just what I wanted'),
(2811, 2, 1, 1, '2016-08-03', 'How could this get such good ratings and burn everything? I really wanted to like this toaster oven but it was huge let down.  There were so many good reviews on Amazon but I\'m not sure who is writing them or if they are for  old models?  It burns everything I cook (toast, baked salmon, egg rolls).  The turn dial is hard to adjust.  It either under-cooks or over-cooks almost everything.  None of the cook settings seem accurate.  My previous B&D toaster oven was great.  What happened?.'),
(2812, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-12', 'Replaced out microwave for this Threw out the microwave to embrace clean eating/living. I was skeptical at first because with kids you sometimes need things fast. Well this little baby cooks up quick. We LOVE it and it didn\'t take long to adjust our timing and get used to this new/old way of cooking! _'),
(2813, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-29', 'GOOD TO GO Excellent product. I like that way it works.'),
(2814, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Love my Keurig! Love my Keurig and how fast it is!! The coffee is yummy too! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(2815, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-16', 'It\'s inexpensive and it does the trick! I puzzled over whether or not to spend upwards of $250 for a convection toaster oven.  I decided to save myself the money and go for this one because it was highly rated.  I\'m glad i did. Some people say they\'re confused by the three knobs - here\'s the quick and dirty explanation: The top knob controls the top element, the middle knob controls the bottom element, and the bottom knob is the timer. The various combinations of the top and bottom elements create the bake, broil and toast function. The timer sets how long your food is exposed to the various combos.  Pretty simple. Pros: at $30, you can\'t beat the price It toasts like a champ (better than our toaster) It broils pretty well too I haven\'t used the baking function, so I can\'t yet speak to that. easily removable crumb tray makes cleanup easier. Cons: It doesn\'t pull out the rack when you open the door.  Not a huge deal, but you\'ll need to keep tongs or hot pads handy The cook tray isn\'t nonstick  - easily remedied with aluminum foil. The glass on the top is exposed when you open the door - be careful! I got a nice little burn by accidentally brushing it after broiling. My own stupid fault for not paying closer attention. Overall I think this is a great value for quick meals when you don\'t want to fire up your oven.'),
(2816, 12, 1, 1, '2016-08-15', 'Not a good safety product does not have a shut off on ... Not a good safety product does not have a shut off on the oven and that make it very dangerous don\'t buy it!.'),
(2817, 5, 1, 2, '2015-02-15', 'Only worked for FIVE months! Made good coffee for five months.  Unfortunately stopped working at all.  Bought this because of the good reviews, but it seems like a coffee maker should last at least a year or two.'),
(2818, 4, 1, 3, '2016-02-11', 'Fantastic!  Until it broke. This is a really great appliance.  The controls aren\'t overly complicated, it is big enough to actually bake things in, and it looks good. You can move the rack around to fit the item you\'re cooking...I\'ve found that for baking, I like to flip the rack upside down, but for toasting I keep it up. Why only 3 stars? Because after only a couple of years of use the front element started to crack, and the split has continued to grow. I have read so many reports of this that I\'m surprised Cuisinart hasn\'t done something to address it.  So...it\'s out of warranty, it\'s broken, but I love it.  Still haven\'t decided if I\'m going to throw more money away replacing it, or get a different model that I don\'t like as much.'),
(2819, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-11', 'Basic but reliable. Basic but pretty reliable so far.  I like that it has a removable tray to catch the crumbs and melted things that drop to the bottom.'),
(2820, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-08', 'One shot will do it This is a great little device for one shot smoothies. I have a larger blender that I used to use but that made so much product I couldn\'t drink it all. here I can make just enough for one serving and that will keep my hunger pangs at bay.'),
(2821, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'the coffee machine I can make through everyday without common human necessity but not this coffee maker. I need it everyday especially when its breakfast and snack time'),
(2822, 3, 1, 5, '2014-11-26', 'it just got dirty enough to where it was easier to replace it ... I bought this to replace my existing one.  Not that the existing one stopped working, I have had it and used it daily for years.  In all honesty, it just got dirty enough to where it was easier to replace it at this price!  I am giving the old one to a friend in need.  The only disappointing thing is that the old  one came with a round pizza pan that fits the oven.  Also, the pans that come with it are aluminum and need to be replaced pretty quickly with something a bit more high quality.  I have never found a pizza pan that fits this unit......'),
(2823, 7, 3, 5, '2015-12-09', 'Yes it\'s good I brew tea in it also. Just take out the filter and put the bag in. Works great'),
(2824, 3, 1, 2, '2016-01-20', 'Two Stars The outside gets very hot when in use.'),
(2825, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-29', 'Five Stars Very easy to clean,.'),
(2826, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-24', 'Very good quality This coffee maker deserves a 5 star. It makes a great quality of coffee. If you are looking for quality and low budget, this is the coffee maker to choose.'),
(2827, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'From a use standpoint, these are great. I know these units eventually wear out, since the heating tubes will start to unravel.  However, in the mean time, they work so well.  I\'ve bought 4 of them so far, two of which I gave as gifts. Makes toast nicely; bakes nicely; NO TIMER (which is what I WANT)I\'m a big boy, and can determine when I want to start and stop baking. I have a friend who has a competing brand, and she constantly complains the timer ran out, and the meal didn\'t finish baking: so she has to set a timer, to know when to go out and rewind that unit.  Plus, she complains the handle on her unit gets hot.  I\'ve had NO TROUBLE with hot handles on this unit. Yes, I recommend it, warts & all.'),
(2828, 7, 3, 5, '2016-03-08', 'IT IS A GREAT LITTLE ITEM .... MAKES GREAT COFFEE TOO'),
(2829, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-11', 'Quick, convenient and fresh This is a great brewing system if you want something quick, convenient and fresh. It is not ideal for company or house guest who consume a lot of coffee because K-cups can get expensive. We had a little trouble getting the \"add more water\" icon to leave when we were first setting up the system but have not had this problem since. The coffee is strong and fresh. Both of which I really like. The water level seems to require a higher level than I thought was necessary. It seems like I need to refill it after almost every cup. But for what it is, it is a good product. Perfect for my office and a well needed break. I received this product free for testing.'),
(2830, 12, 1, 1, '2014-02-11', 'Junk I bought this in June 2013. It stopped working properly in February 2014. The tray is difficult to wash, the material is weird and stains incredibly easy. It\'s like the old cookie trays but worse. It seems to toast unevenly in the toaster-oven. Also, the few times we used the oven portion the items started to burn at about half the time the directions indicated they be cooked for. The toaster function is a joke, the bar that holds up the bread bent so now toast slides down and waffles and bagels roll to one side. Now every time I toast bread or waffles, they fold in half and slide down the side to get stuck on the teeth of the bar. I have to unplug it and fish everything out of there. It was barely tolerable for the last couple of weeks, really limping it along. Today I just shredded a waffle trying to get it out and I\'m ordering a new toaster. The idea was so cool, toaster and toaster oven- but really it\'s not great at either.'),
(2831, 1, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'Busy mornings? Keurig is for you. I love my teal Keurig! I like to consider myself a coffee snob and was completely opposed to them for a long time. We usually make coffee in a Chemex, but I recently got a new job, so my mornings are rushed. I don\'t have time to go through the entire Chemex process. My Keurig brews me a nice, hot cup of coffee within a couple minutes, so I have time to enjoy it and get ready! As long as you find kcups that are of good quality, the coffee will be good! My only complaint is that the amount it brews is not equivalent to the amount ounces it says it\'s brewing.'),
(2832, 8, 1, 2, '2015-07-09', 'Two Stars no frill what so ever but works'),
(2833, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'I\'m not qualified to give a review yet, but ... I\'m not qualified to give a review yet, but I can say how impressed I am by Black and Decker\'s customer service. The last digit on the oven display was only partially visible, B&D replaced the oven in just a few days with no further questions asked.'),
(2834, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-13', 'Great coffee maker The perfect coffee maker for any family. Works like a charm and I LOVE the brew from this machine. Thumbs up!'),
(2835, 6, 1, 4, '2016-05-28', 'Good but not perfect Very well made and attractive as pictured.  But...toasting is not even on both sides.'),
(2836, 3, 1, 5, '2015-04-07', 'Yes.  Just Yes. Great machine.  I use it every day for toast, cooking or baking.  I love the convection option.  This is my second Black and Decker convection oven.  The first one did have something fall on the heating element, I reached out to Black and Decker  and they sent me a new one straight away.  The take away here is that it is a tiny oven, don\'t cook drippy things, crumbly things or saucy things on the wire rack - use a tray just as you would in a full size oven.  Love it.  Would buy again.  It is a great price point for the things it offers, I think better than the perceived \"higher-end\" brands. Great item!'),
(2837, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-22', 'This Toaster Deep Fall 2012. Just before the election. We travelled to Woodstock Valley CT to break the seal on the only couple more averse than us, Papa and Linda-Loo, and the foliage was only less believable than, apparently, Last Week. They had this toaster/oven. Tropical Storm (Hurricane) Sandy hit. We all take for granted \"our freedoms\" until we have to do without them for a few hours. Living where they do, they have a generator, but during the interim hours without power, what I missed was This Toaster.'),
(2838, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'Easy to use Easy to use.  Volumes easy to measure and the temperature is perfect.  Would recommend backing it up with a Medelco Replacement Carafe, which can be ordered through Amazon.'),
(2839, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Five Stars Perfect for house guests. Easy to use, clean and store!'),
(2840, 6, 1, 1, '2015-04-03', 'Melted my cabinet on the first use I was looking for a basic toaster and chose this one based on the good reviews. When it arrived, I was pleased--it looked nice, the slots were plenty big and it didn\'t take up a huge chunk of real estate on the counter. But upon the very first use this toaster got HOT, particularly the back and metal around the slots. Not just warm, but sizzle your skin hot. It actually began melting the laminate coating off the cabinets above the toaster after one toasting cycle. (See photos.) Should a utensil or plastic bag accidentally fall and make contact with it when heating this would be a huge fire hazard, never mind the kids burning themselves trying to get toast out. I\'ve had plenty of inexpensive toasters and none have functioned this way, so it was returned quickly.'),
(2841, 10, 1, 2, '2015-12-04', 'I\'ve only used this probably 20x or less and it ... I\'ve only used this probably 20x or less and it just broke while making a smoothie with frozen strawberries, almond milk and protein mix. I don\'t think I can fix this because the motor has come apart from the blender. I guess you get what you pay for_.'),
(2842, 7, 3, 5, '2014-05-31', 'I love this product. Very easy to use. Clean up is a snap. I just rinse the coffee stand with water and wipe down the rest with a damp cloth. It looks nice on my counter too.'),
(2843, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-31', 'Easy to clean Easy to clean, easy to operate, and great coffee. This replaces another Hamilton Beach that wore out.  Hoping to get as much service out of this one. Great machine at any price, but especially great at the Amazon price!'),
(2844, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-14', 'Five Stars Its only got one button, even I cant mess this up.'),
(2845, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-18', 'Keurig K250 2.0 Review - Attention coffee lovers I recently bought a Keurig K250 2.0 after moving into my new home. This review will cover my experiences good and bad with the product. If you are a coffee lover or drink coffee regularly you may be interested in my experiences. I, myself, am a daily coffee drinker always looking for the easiest, cheapest, and most effective way to get my caffeine fix. The Keurig 2.0 has made this desire better, and I think it will assist other coffee lovers as well. Ease of Use Have you ever found yourself wasting time, money, and effort making a whole pot of coffee in the morning only to take a fraction of it with you for the day? These troubles end with the Keurig 2.0 as you can easily make a single serving of coffee to fuel your day. Not only can you make a great brew, you can also spend little time cleaning up afterwards. The Keurig disposable filter cups can simply be pitched after use. If you choose to take the more economic route, no problem; Keurig makes a reusable filter to enjoy caffeine beverages time and time again. Appearance and Functionality The appliance itself is sleek, classy, and an attractive complement to other appliances in any kitchen. The product features a flawless touch screen display, giving it a modern and sophisticated feel. This display is the communication center for brew choices, the status of your brew, and issues the machine may detect. This feature can come in handy if/when there may be an issue with the system; although, I have not had any issues with its functionality. This brewer is not as wide as other Keurig models, so if youre like me this is convenient with limited counter space. Versatility You may be thinking, But what if I want to make more than just a single serving when company is over? The Keurig K250 2.0 also comes with the capability of use a carafe that holds up to four cups of coffee. The versatility and convenience of this Keurig has made my life much easier in the mornings. After all, a good morning routine and caffeine jolt will start any day off on the right foot. Keurigs Room for Improvement  Only includes 8oz and 10oz brewing options.  Does not include 2.0 reusable filter.  Packaging does not effectively communicate to the consumer that the 2.0 reusable filters are different from all other Keurig models.  Unit does not come with the carafe or a reusable filter specifically for the carafe. So far I have not had any issues with the functionality of the unit, and luckily the touch screen display has the ability to notify me in case a problem may arise. If youre like me and want an easy, effective, and economically efficient way to get your caffeine jolt in the morning, the Keurig K250 2.0 is a wise investment. I have enjoyed this appliance and I believe any other coffee junkie will too. Good luck, and happy brewing!.'),
(2846, 12, 1, 2, '2014-03-28', 'Keep looking - there\'s got to be something better I bought this toaster oven to keep at my work and was thrilled that it had both the functionality of a toaster and an oven. However, once I started using it, I wished I\'d kept looking around. I had only used it for a couple months (not daily) when the toaster part on top no longer worked. When you push the handle down to \"toast\", it won\'t stay down. So, I have to toast my bread in the oven part - which doesn\'t toast evenly. I tried heating up some leftover pizza and had to cut the slices in half because the \"oven\" part is really small. The heating elements on the top and the wire rack are so close that sometimes my food burns because it touches the top. In summary - the food can\'t be too long, too high or too wide (the door won\'t stay closed). The only good thing I can say is it heats up quickly.'),
(2847, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-20', 'Five Stars This is a very good toaster oven. Very easy to use'),
(2848, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-26', 'Five Stars Makes very good coffee. I am satisfied with this product.'),
(2849, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-19', 'Good coffee pot For a bunch of guests this coffee pot provides good coffee promptly with clever features that make making one or more pots fun to make.'),
(2850, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-09', 'Five Stars A cheap version but very reliable and takes the place of my much larger and now retired toaster oven'),
(2851, 9, 1, 2, '2016-11-22', 'JUNK, unless you like coffee all over the place. Just got this coffee maker and I ran 2 full pots of clear water (no coffee grounds) and 2 half pots (no coffee grounds) to make sure it was clear of any dust & etc.  After each cycle I would empty into a coffee mug and each and every time, the water came out in 3 different streams and splatter the sides of pot.  In addition, the water reservoir drips into the drip tray during and after brew cycle. Cuisinart is like Cuisinart used to be with top quality products.  They don\'t even pack an owner\'s manual.'),
(2852, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-12', 'Five Stars works great.'),
(2853, 7, 3, 1, '2014-01-07', 'This unit only worked two weeks with just 5 cups done. On cup number six no power. Beware of this unit. I wish I would have listen to the bad review.'),
(2854, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-12', 'Easily my favorite coffee maker Love this coffee maker. No plastic tastes, even first pot. No spillage when pouring a cup AT ALL.Easily programmable. My favorites: The wheels on the bottom, and the removable water reservoir. Everything on this thing was very well thought out. Can\'t beat it!'),
(2855, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-07', 'Love it! Just got this last week.  I was concerned about the small size, but it still fits two pieces of pizza and get hot much faster because of the small size to heat.  Great little toaster oven especially for the price.'),
(2856, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-07', 'Five Stars so convenient, fresh coffee by the cup.'),
(2857, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-28', 'Great blender I have this blender since my college years 2009. I still have it and it works great. I bought other expensive blenders that I had to throw away but this one never fails.'),
(2858, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-26', 'Four Stars I like the way you fill water and that the spout does not spill like other coffee pots.'),
(2859, 3, 1, 4, '2016-07-18', 'Otherwise it\'s fine. Door swings open too far if there is nothing to stop it. Otherwise it\'s fine.'),
(2860, 12, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'They love it. Ordered one each for wife. sister and mother. They love it.'),
(2861, 4, 1, 1, '2016-04-28', 'they sent a lot of recipes that said to line ... they sent a lot of recipes that said to line the pan with foil but very clearly said not to use foil so I returnded it.'),
(2862, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-09', 'I love my blender I love my blender. It\'s the perfect size. Blends and mixes everything perfectly. I make green smoothies with mixed berries and it gets the job done. I love that it\'s small and portable and you can wrap the cord around the bottom of it for those mornings I\'m in a rush and have to blend when I get to work. The description says it\'s red. Mine is the color depicted in the picture which I prefer over red. It\'s my favorite color FUSCHIA'),
(2863, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-29', 'Looks Good and Gets the Job Done I\'m very happy with this coffee pot. Have had it For about 6 months. I let myself get confused choosing a coffee maker to buy after reading so many reviews, esp. so many negative reviews on every pot available. Some complaints are legit, like if it breaks soon after you get it, but I wonder at some of the exacting critiques and disappointments by some reviewers of their $50 coffee pot. Are they ever really satisfied with anything? This makes a perfectly fine, hot cup of coffee. I set it to Bold because that is how I like it, and it makes good Bold coffee. I set it to Regular once to see the difference, and it was definitely less Bold and more Regular. I havent used the 1-4 cup feature, but nice to have it. I like the narrow shape of this coffee maker, and the stainless/black material. It looks nice. Very happy with the blue backlight on clock. Steam does rise from the top of maker when it is brewing, not an issue for me but may be for some. Maker is lightweight so easy to pull out from under counter. I thought I would use the removable tank feature. Its nice to have it, but I just fill the pot with water and pour it in the tank. I like the push button swing-out feature for the filter. Some say it brews too slowly on Bold. But I turn it on, cook breakfast, and when I\'m finished cooking there is enough brewed coffe to fill 2 large cups. It has the feature that lets you pour in the middle of brewing without spillage. I\'ve never had to wait. Not sure what else to say. It looks good and gets the job done!'),
(2864, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-03', 'Food tastes better heated in one of these than a microwave Food tastes better heated in one of these than a microwave. A bit difficult to clean when food drops onto the heating coils.'),
(2865, 4, 1, 4, '2016-09-02', 'Great little toaster oven. I love my toaster oven. Just wish it were a little bigger. Use it all the time, though.'),
(2866, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-18', 'It\'s a Keurig,  but somewhat overpriced A very nice sized Keurig product for tight spaces  on the counter. It is somewhat overpriced for its size  and features, but they\'re practically the only game in town.  Look for significant discounts or sales before buying, since they are out there.'),
(2867, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-10', 'Five Stars Awesome!!!'),
(2868, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-21', 'Good and suits my needs This coffee pot is good and suits my needs. I\'ve been using it for 2 weeks now and I can\'t really say that I have any complaints about it.'),
(2869, 2, 1, 1, '2015-06-10', 'One Star Impossible to properly time anything. Burns things all the time.'),
(2870, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-14', 'Five Stars Very nice oven'),
(2871, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'Five Stars works great and stays cool to touch on the outside'),
(2872, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-06', 'Very good coffee maker for the money Very good coffee maker for the money. I am all about value for my dollar. This hit the spot. Simple, easy to clean, looks good and last but not least it makes good coffee'),
(2873, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-18', 'Five Stars Perfect'),
(2874, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'LOVE MY KEURIG <3 Ive now had my Keurig for two weeks, and I LOVE IT! This is my first Keurig, but Ive used one before (my mother has had one for four or five years). Im a college student living at home, and I have to wake up very early in the morning, so Im usually in a hurry to get out the door. I have the Sandy Pearl color, and let me tell you, it looks absolutely beautiful in my room! (I love the ability to pick from many colors!) I wouldve chosen Turquoise, but Im hoping to take this with me to my apartment after I graduate, so I chose a neutral color. The heat up, in my opinion, is very quick. I plug my Keurig in, and it begins heating while I start getting ready. Once the sound stops, I put in my favorite cup or use a re-fillable cup and place a tea bag inside. There are many sizes and custom brewing options, which is great because I have so many different kinds of cups and mugs. Some only can hold 4-6oz. and others can hold 10oz. or more. I love the touch screenIts elegant AND easy! While heating and brewing make a decent amount of noise, its much quieter than the one my mother has. My little sisters room is adjacent to mine, and its never woke her up yet! The beverages are always extremely hot, which is great, considering that some days my cup sits there a while before Im ready to grab it, and I think that attributes to how well it brews bags of tea. Ive been pleasantly surprised with how much flavor of tea has made it into my mug without steeping. Now for the cons_ There arent many, but the ones it has, I feel, are pretty important. 1) Several of my travel mugs cannot fit under it (and yes, that is with the tray removed). My solution has been to place a different, smaller cup underneath the Keurig and transfer it into my travel cup afterwards. Its a nuisance, but it works. Luckily, for me, I dont use travel mugs every day, so its not that big of a deal. 2) Theres no auto-off feature. This is the biggest frustration for me. I have to unplug my Keurig after every use to conserve energy. One day I left it on and noticed it DID turn off, BUT then I did the same experiment two other days and it stayed on all day long_ (10+ hours) All in all, Im extremely satisfied with my purchase. The cons are nothing that cant be fixed with a few extra steps on my end, which in the end, doesnt matter as much. This little thing is still faster and easier than stopping by the coffee shop or boiling hot water on the stove for tea. Love this little gem! **Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!**'),
(2875, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-05', 'Perfectly simple. Great coffee, fast & hot! Simple & straightforward. Love that the water container can be washed & that it\'s EASY to access & refill. Coffee brews quickly & can be set for \'bold\'. The carafe is a GREAT design ~ zero drips & is nice & sturdy. This is a great coffeemaker for our purposes. Returned a Keurig & got this ~ & when the need arises, will buy another HB!'),
(2876, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-05', 'This is a great coffee pot. I like the price and the fact that it uses the Kcups. It brews slower than the keurig but not enough to bother me.'),
(2877, 10, 1, 4, '2015-09-13', 'Perfect for the price Perfect for the Bachelor life. It won\'t chop things up perfectly, but if all you want to do is mix & blend some fruits, veggies or protein powder it\'s adequate.  It will leave some small chunks sometimes so I advise not trying to use for blended ice drinks'),
(2878, 5, 1, 1, '2015-12-02', 'One Star Did not meet expectations'),
(2879, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-11', '... for a month now and me and my wife love it! Have had it for a month now and me and my wife love it!! Makes a great cup of coffee! Easy to fill with water and coffee grinds! Only weird thing is the lip on the pitcher keeps a few drops of coffee from pouring out. Never seen that in a coffee pitcher before. Not a big deal though!'),
(2880, 11, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'Five Stars Use it everyday and love it'),
(2881, 7, 3, 1, '2016-04-07', 'This would be a great product if it actually worked longer than a few months. I purchased the coffeemaker and after 3 months it started to leak. I thought maybe it was user error so I purchased another one about 4 months later, my daughter used it also. Same problem with the leaking, then it stopped working. Since I have purchased 2 within 1 year I will not purchase a 3rd. I\'m glad it works well for others, however, I do not recommend it.'),
(2882, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-06', 'Five Stars This is the best coffeemaker I have ever owned. I love it!'),
(2883, 10, 1, 5, '2016-06-04', 'the little mixer that could I bought this little guy in January, 2012, Amazon is telling me, and it has served me well just about daily ever since.  I was just mixing up a protein shake tonight and I thought, \"This little guy merits some praise!\"  Best thing I\'ve bought for under $25 in ... well since $25 was worth a lot more than it seems to be these days.  I do a lot of frappuccinos -- this works great with ice cubes, it can pulverize frozen Milky Ways np, and in fact despite my occasional skepticism it\'s been up to every mixing/blending task which has come my way since I bought it.  (I have a couple of more elaborate and CERtainly more expensive blenders on top of my kitchen cabinet, but I never take them down.)  And it\'s about the size of a milkshake canister (ie, a large glass), so you can just chug from it if you ever want to save yourself a dirty dish.  You GO, little mixer!'),
(2884, 10, 1, 3, '2016-04-07', 'Not too impressed Used this twice. First time shake came out amazing. Second time could smell burning although still does the job.'),
(2885, 3, 1, 3, '2015-11-06', 'Decent If you are looking for a simple toaster oven then this will work, however it lacks in appeal. The unit heats up fast and on point, the failure is in the control panel. The buzzer to notify that items are done cooking is very quite. If the fridge, and dishwasher is on you will not hear the buzzer. The controls are very cheap feeling. The preset settings for cooking must be meant for food stored in liquid nitrogen. The time presets are way too long for most common items like potatoes and pizza.'),
(2886, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-28', 'Five Stars Blends vitamin smoothies well!'),
(2887, 6, 1, 4, '2015-09-21', 'Good value So okay... It\'s a toaster.... And an inexpensive one at that. I am not typically a guy who searches out the cheapest thing especially when it comes to appliances or \"durable goods\". But with a toaster, I thought I would just give it a try. This toaster replaced an earlier, far more expensive, upscale model that performed just \"okay\" and lasted about ten years. Since I no longer really care about what visitors think about my purchase decisions and I am no longer interested in \"keeping up with the ...\", I figured this toaster would be fine.... as long as it worked the way it was supposed to. The one it replaced was also a Cuisinart..... long slot, beautiful finish, high tech controls, heated with fancy glow bulbs.... Well, the bulbs gave up and it seemed such a waste of time and dollars to try to replace them... especially since the toaster never performed nearly as well as it should have (considering the original price...).  So I decided to go the opposite way this time.  This Cuisinart toaster looks good, toasts two slices at a time, will accept and toast bagels and English muffins, and works the way it was designed (at least so far...!!). Toasting normal sandwich bread is easy. Set the darkness to the center (#4) and push the lever/handle down. Shortly you will have toast. Both sides toasted to a close approximation of each other.  If you toast other bread styles like the more upscale bakery breads (7-grain, Oatmeal-honey, All-grain, etc., ...) then you will probably need to set the control to #5 to get a satisfactory \"crunch\" on your toast. English muffins take longer (in all toasters..). Bagels toast fine too. If you use the special bagel \"feature\" (button..) then the bagel will toast mostly on one side.... And as long as you put the bagel into the toaster the same way each time, it should be mostly satisfactory.  I like the defrost setting... It works. I will usually keep a loaf or two of bread in the freezer... The defrost setting allows you to defrost and toast quickly. Should be a relatively simple process ... and apparently it is because it works the way it is supposed to. I like the wide slots and the way the toaster keeps the bread centered (mostly... as long as you aren\'t toasting really thin bread..). The cord is short, but that is to be expected because the law requires it. It can be routed around several little hooks on the bottom of the toaster so that it exits out from under the base on the side or the rear... whichever you prefer. Overall, I\'m happy.  If it quits tomorrow, I will send it back. If it quits after a few years, I will have received my money\'s worth of use.  No complaints.'),
(2888, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-18', 'VERY easy to over-toast bread Unfortunately, VERY easy to over-toast bread. Keep the dial set very light.'),
(2889, 7, 3, 5, '2014-05-14', 'I got my hamilton beach single serve as a Christmas present this past year. So I\'ve been using it now for roughly 6 months. And believe me when I say...I USE IT. I\'m shocked I haven\'t worn it out by now. For the price...it\'s great. I don\'t love that you have to measure out the water based on the coffee cup you want to you but...hey...you DO have to. And if you measure it out...you won\'t have a crazy, leaky mess. I have had absolutely no issues with my coffee maker and would recommend it to anyone that wants a keurig but doesn\'t have the money for one. It makes a cup of coffee in less than two minutes and it\'s great! I love it!!!'),
(2890, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-25', 'My old coffee maker bit the dust some time ago and I switched to instant coffee. Its good but just not the same as brewed coffee. So I went in search of a good single serve coffee maker. The K-cups looked like a great idea but the Keurig coffee makers priced at almost $200.00 turned me off right away. I almost gave up until I found The Hamilton Beach Flexbrew. The price was right and it does all a Kuerig does for a fraction of the cost. I\'ve had mine for a week now and I love it !! Its light weight easy to use and makes a great cup of coffee. I\'ve tried fresh ground coffee and the K- cups so far and both work equally well even with just plain tap water. Looking for the pods next and just dying to try tea and hot chocolate too. Don\'t believe all the bad reviews this is a great product....Thanks Walmart !!!'),
(2891, 6, 1, 3, '2014-07-10', 'it\'s a bit better. Whatever happened to sturdy things Compared to a Cuisinart toaster I bought a few years ago, this feels a little tinny.  The handle that takes the bread down into the toaster is dinky.  I am not thrilled.  But, compared to the ones you find out there in stores, it\'s a bit better. Whatever happened to sturdy things?'),
(2892, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-21', 'Had the unit for about a year. I use ... Had the unit for about a year. I use it a couple times a week and hasn\'t broken down yet. Small, but packs a big punch so to speak.'),
(2893, 5, 1, 2, '2016-04-22', 'Faceplate Breaks The first time the coffee marker was used the faceplate came off when pressing the button to open the basket to load the coffee. Figured, no big deal. It happens. Returned it and got another one. The coffee marker worked great for a few weeks and the same thing, the faceplate broke off when opening the coffee basket.'),
(2894, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-01', 'Great product ! Great product !'),
(2895, 11, 1, 2, '2014-05-19', 'Doesnt work well This toaster is very slow to heat up, very small.  not pleased with this purchase.  takes forever to bake things'),
(2896, 6, 1, 3, '2015-04-29', 'Three Stars Toast unevenly'),
(2897, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-26', 'Five Stars Love my toaster!'),
(2898, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-07', 'ACCESS TO THE WQTER AND COFFEE COMPARTMENT IS EASY AND WELL THOUGHT OUT THE COFFEE MAKER IS OUTSTANDING. ACCESS TO THE WQTER AND COFFEE COMPARTMENT IS EASY AND WELL THOUGHT OUT. THE FEATURES ARE WELL PLANNED AND HELPS GIVE THE BREWED COFFEE A WONDERFUL TASTE. I WOULD HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS PRODUCT.'),
(2899, 4, 1, 5, '2016-07-14', 'I love my toaster over I love my toaster over. It\'s good for everything. I use it for warming, toasting, and light baking. Great value as well.'),
(2900, 6, 1, 3, '2014-02-20', 'They don\'t make them like they used to I bought this toaster as a housewarming gift and it was perfect at first but after 2 months of use the levers don\'t quite work the same.  They\'re kind of cheap, you feel like you might break them and sometimes you have to push the right one down 2 or 3 times in order to get it to stay down. (I\'m assuming that\'s the one that gets used the most but still it shouldn\'t show wear after 2 months.) The heating element works the fine and is consistent so it does the job so far. I don\'t believe the price is justified for this product, especially since I don\'t think the quality is all that great.'),
(2901, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-04', 'Great Coffee Maker I decided to go back to an \"old school\" style coffee maker, because k-cups for a family of 4 cost a fortune each month and feels wasteful. I\'m also becoming more of a coffee snob (sorry, but true), and I\'ve always known that even my favorite k-cups don\'t provide quite the same quality of flavor as freshly ground. As for the machine specifics, first, it has all the same features as many other machines: programmable, automatic shut-off, different coffee strength options, nice thick handle on the carafe, pretty stainless steel, and pause dripping while you sneak a cup mid-brew. I love the pause feature - you just pull the carafe out and it knows to stop dripping until you put it back. Genius. Additionally, this one has a front-entry filter compartment, instead of a lift-top. I like that. It has a lift-out filter basket, so you don\'t burn your fingers removing a hot, wet coffee filter. Then you just tip the basket into the trash to dump the used filter. There are also 3 options to choose from for your \"keep warm\" temperature after brewing. The only improvement I would wish for - and this isn\'t a big enough deal for me to delete a star - would be to move the water tank from the back to the side, like on the Keurig. I have to move this machine slightly out from underneath the top cabinets to reach the water tank. This somewhat defeats the convenience of the front-loading filter basket, but I\'m working on finding an arrangement where I don\'t have to move it (because hey, I\'m a problem-solver).'),
(2902, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-03', 'Great coffee maker What a great coffee maker, swivels-great idea! Works great, easy to use.'),
(2903, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-29', 'Excellent coffee pot This pot is great.  Only complaint is it runs slightly slow - but the coffee taste is wonderful, the setup is easy, it looks great, and I love the open resevoir in the back.  Much easier and faster to fill it than a regular style pot.  Very nice.'),
(2904, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-21', 'Great value Came packaged great Great value Came packaged great, neat and did not have any broken parts Heats up quickly for toasts/ salmon cooking even! Bottom catch all unfortunately was stained by cheese -drip incident /: Stain cannot seem to be removed now. Initially was like a non-stick pan texture.'),
(2905, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-31', 'Love this little guy. Got this to blend protein but I found it\'ll power through frozen fruit and ice to make a smoothie, too! Perfect size for blending up eggs for scrambling, too.'),
(2906, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Don\'t stand in line waiting for that perfect cup #getKeurig Simplicity, who could ask for more?  Well, I could! More coffee that is.  With the ease of use that this machine offers you too will be wanting to make cup after cup of your choice of deliciously brewed coffee. Warning:  Very, very, habit forming.  But that\'s a good thing! Seriously, don\'t waste your money (like I initially did) on subpar units mimicking the Keurig \"system\" by the original and buy the 2.0, it\'s AWESOME! I want to give a huge shout out to the good people of Keurig for supplying me with the free pods for this review.  The Company is amazing, they care about their customer, and their coffee is tops.  Thank you Keurig. Now people, go get your own!'),
(2907, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'Overall, a good coffee maker for the price. Pros  I like the size and this was my main reason for buying this coffee maker. It hold around 32 ounces which is four to six cups depending on your definition of a cup.  The coffee is plenty strong and the temperature of the coffee is about right. It gets warmer if you leave it on the hot plate. The coffee tastes good if you use quality coffee grounds.  I liked the price of the coffee maker. Cons  Its easy to spill a few drops if you are not careful to pour slowly.  I dont like the design where the showerhead is built into the water reservoir lid. This keeps you from opening the lid under the cabinet. All coffee makers seem to come this way today so I am not sure it is fair to reduce my rating because of this. I am sure most customers would rather pay the extra to have the old design. Features the coffee maker is lacking but would increase the price.  Brew pause feature. This is not something I use because it makes the last cup weaker than the first.  A programmable brew start, auto shutoff and digital clock.  Some small coffee makers have these features but the ones I considered made less coffee. Other comments  It takes around 10 minutes to make a full 32 once pot of coffee. I not sure how this compares to other coffee makers.  I would buy this model again if I had to make the decision over again.'),
(2908, 9, 1, 1, '2015-12-03', 'Moronic Engineering You won\'t trip over this power cord...or be able to use it..because it\'s 1 MAYBE 2 inches long. Why even put one on the thing if you need to purchase your own extension cord just to get it to plug in? What a joke. Idiots!'),
(2909, 7, 3, 1, '2016-01-20', 'These coffee makers are pure junk. I had one and it quit working after two weeks. I returned it and decided to get another one because that surely was a fluke. Now today the new one is doing the same thing. Either will not turn on or the light will come on but no water/coffee comes out. I don\'t know how they can continue to sell these things. BE SURE TO KEEP YOUR RECEIPT IF YOU PURCHASE ONE OF THESE.'),
(2910, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'My favorite type of coffee pot - no carafe to break My favorite type of coffee pot - no carafe to break.  Just put your cup under it and press to fill with coffee.'),
(2911, 1, 1, 2, '2015-06-25', 'My K200 is getting returned This thing feels and sounds cheap. The handle mechanism feels like lightweight plastic and it feels like I am breaking it when I try to shut the handle. The user experience with the K200 is unsatisfactory. I own an older model that feels much more solid. Annoyances: -Old Keurig was push one button and get a full cup. New K200 makes me touch the dinky arrow in the tiny screen (from 1994?) to set a 10 ounce size that will fill my normal coffee cup. Then I have to press the physical brew button to brew the cup. Again, not a deal breaker but really annoying because it is totally unnecessary. Who approved the dinky arrow and dinky little screen? -Can\'t set large cup as default size. I have to tell it not to brew half a cup. Every time. Do the designers actually use this Keurig or pick up their coffee at Starbucks in the morning? -Lots of weird straining sounds when brewing. Way more so than older Keurig. -Handle mechanism feels cheap. -KCup is set deeper in unit than past Keurigs.This means that you stick your hand inside the Keurig instead of dropping the KCup into the old vertical holder. I then have to pick it out with my fingernails (not pleasant. If you are sharing this Keurig I guess you are sharing fingernail germs). And since cleaning supplies were included with the K200, I fear that this deepset KCup hole needs to be sanitized much more often. -Lots of condensation forms on inside of reservoir lid. When you remove the (ill fitting and weird to shut) lid, water drips on your hand/countertop. No big deal but again I fear bacteria buildup. -This thing is taller than in the past. I can\'t open the handle when unit is under a cabinet.'),
(2912, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-11', 'Five Stars Great'),
(2913, 8, 1, 1, '2016-04-20', 'DO NOT BUY Received as a gift....I liked it....bought one for my Mom.  Then of course mine quit working...4 months in.  Emailed and yes it is covered by 1 year warranty....but you have to send $7.50 processing fee and mail portion of cord back to company as proof....So not really a warranty at all.  You are out  $15 to get your DEFECTIVE coffee maker replaced and new it cost $15.....I will NEVER buy Black and Decker again. What a rip off.  DO NOT BUY!!  WARRANTY IS FALSE ADVERTISING!  They do not stand behind their product and this product is defective!'),
(2914, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-26', '... my last b & d I\'ll be even more happy. If it lasts as long as my last b & d I\'ll be even more happy.'),
(2915, 4, 1, 4, '2015-06-26', 'Four Stars Good product good service'),
(2916, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-22', 'Great coffee maker Great coffee maker! I like the display and options for \"keep warm\" and \"bold brew\". The spinning base makes it easy to fill with water without having to remove the reservoir, but the reservoir is easy to lift off if needed. Others have complained about the blue light on the display screen but I like it - it\'s just enough light to see in the dark morning without having to turn on a bright kitchen light, but it\'s not blinding when I\'m half asleep either.'),
(2917, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-24', 'Great toaster oven This is an upgraded model of a toaster oven that I had used for years.  When we moved three states away my step son took the old one.  Very easy to use and clean.  Plenty of room for a 10\' x 13\' pan and frozen pizza.  I would not hesitate to recommend this to anyone.'),
(2918, 8, 1, 1, '2016-03-11', 'Looking awesome but only a piece of plastic there It is not very useful, and the coffee pot is very easy to be broken. Overall, that was an extremely bad shopping experience.'),
(2919, 10, 1, 3, '2015-02-02', 'Cheap, worked for a year This blender was very cheap and small and that\'s exactly what I wanted for my dorm room. I\'ve continued using it into this year but overall the blender lasted about a year w/ use 4-5 times a week, give or take. Works well but you often need to shake up the cup so that it can blend evenly. If you have the space/can afford it, I would recommend buying a blender that will last longer but for the money I paid and the amount of smoothies I made this was a decent buy.'),
(2920, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Cheap but reliable toaster oven Arrived on time and in great condition. Works great and I use for mostly all my cooking and baking.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(2921, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-26', 'Does the job This was my first order since joining Amazon Prime that did not arrive on time.  It was supposed to be delivered on Friday 8/22.  Amazon showed that it left their facility but UPS did not have it.  So it arrived Monday, 8/25.  Since it was late and we had a use for it over the weekend, I checked our local stores and found the same thing at Meijer for $5 cheaper.  Even with sales tax added it still ended up being $3.25 cheaper than Amazon\'s price.  Did not expect that.  Anyway, we will keep the one from Amazon for a spare, or maybe to use as a gift for some reason. The toaster seems to work quite well.  It is smaller than the one it is replacing so it heats up and gets done quicker, which is nice.  And it does get pretty darn warm on the outside.  Definitely not a good idea to have anything sitting on top of it or very close to it.  Controls are simple to use.  We have only used the toast function so far, so I don\'t know how it does on the other settings.  You do get to listen to the timer run down as the toasting cycle completes, but it isn\'t that bad.  I was toasting a sub sandwich without the drip tray in it.  Bad idea!  Grease dripped on to the bottom heating element and caught on fire.  Caused some smoke but no damage to anything.  The next sandwich I toasted I put the drip tray in and did have to increase the toasting time a bit as the tray deflects the heat from the bottom element from getting directly to the food, but I think it did a better job overall.  The bread wasn\'t dried out and cutting my gums or the roof of my mouth.  Hopefully it lasts longer than the one it is replacing.  If so, it will certainly be worth the investment.'),
(2922, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-05', 'Five Stars Best applianceand the price is unbeatable too'),
(2923, 3, 1, 2, '2016-01-24', 'Printing came off of control panel right away. I have this toaster oven and I\'m very disappointed that the printing all wore off the top of the buttons within the first two months I owned it.  It came right off when I cleaned it.  I\'ve had to write the functions with a sharpie. Other than that, it works great.'),
(2924, 9, 1, 1, '2016-09-06', 'Do not buy this coffee maker. The only way ... Do not buy this coffee maker. The only way to empty the reservoir is the hold down the coffee release lever and watch the coffee trickle out, until it\'s empty. This is very time consuming. Also, the coffee sometimes doesn\'t get hot enough.'),
(2925, 6, 1, 3, '2015-02-20', 'Works well, but does not toast evenly. Works well for the price paid. Nothing has broken so far (I\'ve had it for 6 months). It does however toast unevenly, so if that bothers you, I would spend the extra money and get something of better quality.'),
(2926, 6, 1, 4, '2016-11-28', 'what can I say? Its a toaster, what can I say?.'),
(2927, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-09', 'Five Stars Better than I expected'),
(2928, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-01', 'Brews great coffee I have finally found the ideal coffee maker for me. It brews an excellent cup of coffee and is extremely easy to use. I like that I can remove the pot, even in the middle of the brew cycle, and it doesn\'t drip one drop of coffee. It also looks very nice.'),
(2929, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'Love the product! Great product! Makes the perfect amount of coffee every time!'),
(2930, 7, 3, 5, '2016-03-16', 'One of the things I don\'t like about coffee at home is you make it 10 cups at a time, and it\'s often too weak, or its sat in the pot too long. Using Colombian beans one scoop makes coffee as good as I had to go out for. I got mine, now you get yours!'),
(2931, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', '... recently bought this Keurig K250 and I am in love! I don\'t drink plain coffee so I bought ... I recently bought this Keurig K250 and I am in love! I don\'t drink plain coffee so I bought this to make Chai lattes, iced coffees, Mocha lattes, etc. I love that I get to have my fun drinks for a fraction of what it was costing me to buy at a coffee shop! It\'s a nice size for on my counter, it was easy to set up and it\'s super easy to use. It isn\'t the quietest machine out there but that doesn\'t bother me. Not totally sure how I feel about only being able to use Keurig kcups (no other brands) but so far that has been fine too, since they have so many different options. Apparently the Keurig site and Target have some deals/coupons on those kcups often enough. Overall, I do recommend this Keurig! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(2932, 12, 1, 1, '2015-07-10', 'Toastation ......yuck! The toaster oven broke on July 10, 2015 ............after only 5 months and now it costs more!'),
(2933, 3, 1, 1, '2016-07-15', 'No Good. Came defective.  Back light on display does not come on so I can\'t see the numbers,'),
(2934, 2, 1, 3, '2016-02-18', 'Ok! Good for the price'),
(2935, 8, 1, 5, '2015-10-27', 'Five Stars Perfectly working.'),
(2936, 2, 1, 2, '2016-03-23', 'Two Stars Toast feature quit working after six months.  Now it simply warms bread etc.'),
(2937, 5, 1, 4, '2016-08-30', 'I like that the water tank is removable It\'s a coffee maker, it makes coffee. I like that the water tank is removable, making for easy cleaning. The bight blue LED display stays on all the time which is a little annoying.'),
(2938, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'A Better Brewer Purchased K250 three weeks ago...Simplistic in design and easy to use...Makes excellent single coffee serving  absent any of the preparations of filling a strainer basket and then waiting for the brew cycle to complete...Probably threw out a lot of good coffee with my old pot brewer simply because I just wanted a cup or two...K2 does come with a carafe (purchased separately) so that you can make multiple cups if you wish...Only two negatives I noticed, there is no off/on switch to completely remove power so if you wish to shut the K2 down for a period you have to unplug it and there is currently no reusable pods available although Keurig assures me one will be available by Dec 2015.'),
(2939, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'excellent Love it!!!! The only thing it is bigger than the dimensions they say.'),
(2940, 5, 1, 4, '2014-06-26', 'Makes a good cup of coffee Makes good coffee. Took a few pots to get the right combo of grounds/water for our liking...we like it very strong but not bitter.  No leaking, as some reported.  Only complaint is that if you don\'t completely close the front face (which is sometimes easy to miss, especially in the morning before coffee...and the door itself is a little \"sticky\"), you end up with a flood of water and grounds.  It would be nice if it wouldn\'t allow you to run it unless the face was completely closed.'),
(2941, 2, 1, 3, '2016-04-02', 'better than a microwave I like the old model better. The older model had a slide out pan that was on the OUTSIDE and bottom of this unit allowing for easy and thorough cleaning of crumbs. This one the thin tray is inside and crumbs fall behind, under and in-between. Also the glass door has a small seam where seeds gets stuck. Not impressed with this model but the older one stopped working after 4 years.'),
(2942, 5, 1, 1, '2016-04-06', 'Heating Pad Rusted within 1 Year of Use, Disappointing I had high hopes for this solidly reviewed Coffee Maker from Hamilton Beach, but within 1 year of purchase and regular careful use (I love my coffee machines and treat them well), the heating pad on which the glass carafe sits started to rust and flake off dime-sized bits of metal. At first I thought the flakes were coffee grinds, so I rinsed out my carafe especially well, but it turns out the entire heating pad is falling apart and shedding layers of metal every day. In addition to being unappetizing, this is a major defect. While this coffee maker was not as expensive as Cuisinart models, I previously owned a Cuisinart coffee maker that lasted over 5 years without any problems (and I only moved on from that model because I wanted a machine with an easier-to-fill water canister). After this disappointing experience with Hamilton Beach heating pads, Im going back to Cuisinart because they last much longer and are better quality.'),
(2943, 5, 1, 4, '2016-02-18', 'Good For Smaller Kitchen Nice , good value, not fancy, works well.'),
(2944, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-02', 'I love this mini blender I love this mini blender!  The top part twists off easily for pouring, drinking, or cleaning.  There is indeed a \"burning smell\" if you blend for too long;  I usually blend a bit, wait a few seconds, then blend some more.  I\'ve mostly been making smoothies and the blender blends ice cubes with no problem.'),
(2945, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Five Stars Mixes hot water through filtered coffee beans.'),
(2946, 8, 1, 5, '2015-10-16', 'gb Better than the one I bought before which lasted less than a year.'),
(2947, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-03', 'Five Stars love this but its smaller than i had expected'),
(2948, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-19', 'Five Stars Have used this type coffee maker for years. No coffee pot to break.'),
(2949, 9, 1, 2, '2015-10-28', 'Doesn\'t deliver a tasty cup without experimentation, float/gauge housing impossible to clean Apologies for the lack of a verified review, my girlfriend purchased it on her account nearly a year ago. I struggled with whether to give this a 2 or 3 star rating, as my experience falls between \"don\'t like it\" and  \"it\'s okay\", but I think it\'s better to round down in this case. Like many other reviewers, we gave this a try after breaking a couple of carafes on other machines and finding replacements to be too costly. The concept is great, but it doesn\'t deliver the most important thing: tasty coffee. We haven\'t experienced any leaking or overflowing, but the weak brew it produces is disappointing to say the least. Some experimentation will be required since tastes vary, but we\'ve settled on the following: -For 5 cups or less, use paper + gold filter and 1-4 setting -For 6 and up, use paper filter only One of the weakest aspects of the machine is that it considers 5 oz to be a cup instead of the standard 6 oz. This means that you\'re using an extra tablespoon of coffee to make two 12 oz servings, which still may be weak if you don\'t do it correctly. Some recommend grinding a bit finer, but if we wanted to do stuff like that, we\'d be using a french press and buying whole beans. We don\'t use the water filter since we\'re already filtering at our faucet, and I\'ve wondered if that\'s partly to blame; is the machine depending on it to slow down the water flow? Possibly, but even if it is, I\'m not willing to commit to buying those regularly. I\'ve also wondered about the included gold coffee filter. One with a solid bottom might yield better results, but we\'re already $90 in the hole here, so I\'m less than thrilled about spending more money to get a decent cup of coffee out of this thing. I saw another reviewer mention that they removed the float mechanism entirely since it\'s nearly impossible to clean. I\'d like to do the same, but I\'m hesitant to apply force. Overall? Keep looking. **Update 10/30/2015*** I removed the housing that contains the actual float and the mechanism that controls the gauge. It came out easier than expected, but would be very difficult to reinstall. That said, I have no interest in doing so as the inside of the housing and all parts within were FILTHY. When I say filthy, I mean absolutely covered in black residue, which makes sense as you can\'t really access it even with a bottle brush or something like that. Talk about a design flaw...'),
(2950, 10, 1, 3, '2015-11-05', 'I bought it for the price to use in my ... I bought it for the price to use in my camper. It does a fair job....Not even close to my Nutri bullet, but I knew that when I bought it.'),
(2951, 12, 1, 5, '2016-10-05', 'Five Stars Good product.'),
(2952, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'Five Stars perfect for a single person'),
(2953, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-03', 'This coffee maker is great. The removable reservoir is easy to fill This coffee maker is great. The removable reservoir is easy to fill. The carafe doesn\'t drip and the controls for the warming plate make for a truly hot cup of coffee. Can\'t beat it for the price.'),
(2954, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-24', 'I HAVE HAD THESE COFFEE MAKERS WHEN THEY FIRST CAME OUT OTHER MODELS WERE A LITTLE MORE EXPENSIVE !! HOWEVER !!!!! THEY WORKED THIS IS THE BIGGEST PIECE OF JUNK I HAVE EVER HAD THE FIRST COUPLE OF DAYS IT WAS OK AFTER THAT THE MADE MORE NOISE THAN MY RACE CAR MORE WATER ON COUNTER THAN IN THE CUP SO I CLEANED IT STILL PROBLEMS ONE RIGHT AFTER ANOTHER I WILL NEVER BY OFF BRAND AGAIN AND FOR SURE NOTHING FROM THIS COMPANY I USE MY COFFEE MAKER AT LEAST 6 TO 7 TIMES A DAY I WOULD NOT EVEN WASTE MY TIME RETURNING RIGHT IN THE TRASH AFTER 1 MONTH I WOULD NOT WANT MY ENEMY TO USE IT NEVER MIND MY FRIENDS'),
(2955, 10, 1, 1, '2016-03-09', 'One Star Didn\'t last 2 months would not blend ice at all. Barely blended frozen berries.'),
(2956, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-14', 'Perfect for 2 Works like a charm! My husband and I have a brew every morning now since we don\'t have to clean the pot. Perfect for a couple or small family as you don\'t have to hassle with a kettle.'),
(2957, 12, 1, 4, '2014-07-05', 'Great little toaster AND great little oven I was thinking of buying one of these, but after reading the reviews wasn\'t sure it would work for me. Then I found one at a thrift shop and bought it as a \"trial run.\" I loved it so much, but really wanted the red version, so I bought the red version and use the older (black) one for camping. Addressing some of the issues others have raised: It\'s small: Yes, this is true. But it will fit two good sized slices of pizza and so is big enough for most anything I want to use it for. If you use a toaster oven to cook for a family, it might not work for you, but for a single person it\'s perfect. No broiler: Also true. I find I don\'t miss it, when I want to broil something (not that often) I use my regular oven. No timer: Also also true. But I have a timer on my microwave and also a stand alone timer, so if I need a timer I use one of those. How many timers do you need in the kitchen anyway? Toasts unevenly: Not in my experience. Mine toasts just as evenly as any toaster I\'ve ever owned. PLUS (and this is a big deal) it has a window in front so you can watch your toast and pop it out when it gets the shade you want. Why aren\'t all toasters this way! :) The older version I bought at the thrift store did not have a \"cancel\" button, but this new one does. This lets you turn off the oven or pop up your toast without having to pull on a lever. The tray does hang up a little sometimes, it just takes the right touch to push it in. (This is what gave it 4 stars instead of 5...you\'d think they would have figured this out by now.) Bottom line for me is, this takes up WAY less room than most regular toaster ovens, let alone a toaster oven and separate toaster. It\'s retro cute and easy to clean. It holds any toast I\'ve thrown at it, and it cooks lots of oven-y things so I don\'t have to use the energy or generate the heat from the large oven. So I love my Toastation! It might not work for everyone, but it works for me.'),
(2958, 1, 1, 1, '2015-06-29', 'Would do anything to get my old Keurig back. ... Would do anything to get my old Keurig back. The 2.0 is too loud, my mug doesn\'t fit, can\'t use anything but K cups and drips after use.'),
(2959, 10, 1, 2, '2016-02-23', 'When I received the blender, the handbook inside informed ... When I received the blender, the handbook inside informed me that I could not use it for hot liquids, meat, or cheese products. I don\'t recall seeing this info in the Amazon description. Also, I hoped that the blender would pulverize ice, so that I could makes slushies.'),
(2960, 6, 1, 5, '2014-04-02', 'Fabulous Toaster Both my wife and I really enjoy our new Cuisinart CPT - 142 Compact 4 - Slice Toaster.. It toasts Bagels, Toast and English Muffins to perfection. The old adage, \"You get what you pay for\" is a truism indeed. We thought the price of 50 dollars was fair. Dawn and Phil'),
(2961, 8, 1, 4, '2015-05-29', 'Smaller than expected.  (perhaps bigger on the inside?) Turned out to be much smaller than expected, but it works just fine.  My roommate was being super cheap and he bought this, not realizing he could have gotten a full sized coffee maker for the same price.  However, he only drinks one big cup of coffee in the morning, and this size is just perfect for that.  If you want a basic coffee maker without any bells and whistles, and only makes about 24 ounces of coffee, this is for you.  It looks like the kind they put in hotel rooms.'),
(2962, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-16', 'Meets expectation. Makes good coffee fast, really works good. This is my second so I knew what to expect.'),
(2963, 3, 1, 5, '2014-08-27', 'We would recommend it to anyone This oven is outstanding.  We use it 95% of the time in lieu of the oven in our range.  It is large enough to do a 2 lb. meatloaf or roast a whole chicken.  We would recommend it to anyone.'),
(2964, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-16', 'Five Stars need to get another.  This was a gift'),
(2965, 7, 3, 5, '2015-11-03', 'It\'s so rare anymore for me to bring a product home and feel I got more than expected. This is one of the few purchases I have made in sometime that did just that. I had just purchased one that made bad coffee, smelled like plastic (wouldn\'t go away with several cleanings) and took too long to brew. A couple cleanings (something you should always do) and this was totally ready to go. I like very strong coffee and tried the bold setting. Wow, on this one, bold means bold! Tried the regular setting and found it to be perfect. The coffee taste was excellent. Much better than any coffee maker I have ever owned and certainly beyond expectation. Speed of brewing was a surprise too. Very fast. Bold takes a bit longer as it is supposed to. Still fine. Cleaning is so easy, I found I can dump and clean the filter, wipe and dry out the machine before my coffee could even begin to cool down. It looks nice on the counter and takes up little space. I can use my smaller mug or add a bit more grounds and use my taller travel mug due to the adjustable height base. The cord may be a bit short if you need it a fair distance from the outlet. For me it\'s perfect because I have it right by the outlet and don\'t like the look of a long cord laying on the counter. Will it hold up? Don\'t know yet, but the build seems very solid, giving me no current concerns in that regard. I will be recommending this product to anyone who needs a single serve coffee maker. Excellent product!'),
(2966, 11, 1, 3, '2014-02-15', 'Works Great But TINY! They say you can fit 4 slices of bread in this thing. I don\'t know what kind of bread they\'re talking about.'),
(2967, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Five Stars Very good!!'),
(2968, 6, 1, 3, '2016-03-19', 'Looks nice and I do not like hard toast Only toasts one side of bread. But, I am keeping it.  Looks nice and I do not like hard toast.'),
(2969, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Five Stars Completly satisfied with the product...THNAKS.'),
(2970, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Best bang for the buck in a toaster oven. A very solid unit.  A basic toaster oven, no digital, easy to operate.  A toaster oven for no more than a 4 slice toaster, actually less than some.  Makes toast just right also broils and bakes.  If there is a drawback, the instructions are not very complete, but it\'s such a user friendly appliance you most likely won\'t even need to look at the instructions.'),
(2971, 7, 3, 1, '2016-05-31', 'DO NOT BUY THIS MACHINE. I purchase this on 2015 Nov 08. It stopped working Around 2016 Jan 20. (3 months) Received a new one after paying a small for shipping fee (no other charge), around Jan 31. It stopped working again 2016 May 30. (4 months) Issue: The water does not pump up after boiling = Useless. Do not waste your money. It\'s stressful to deal with warranty and the lack of coffee when you need it and the lack of such for a few days while waiting for replacement? If this happens once, okay, twice... it\'s ridiculous.'),
(2972, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-16', 'Five Stars fantastic love mine'),
(2973, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-24', 'It works fine. Dials are not my favorite design It works fine.  Dials are not my favorite design.  Looks nice on the counter.'),
(2974, 8, 1, 4, '2014-07-02', 'Good, basic little coffee maker I bought this coffee maker at Target about 9 months ago.  It\'s a good little coffee maker for the price.  I\'m happy with it.  It\'s as simple as you can get which is what I wanted. I didn\'t want or need anything with a bunch of bells and whistles. It is easy to clean and fits regular basket filters, which is a plus.  I gave it four stars because for the sake of honesty it does have a few minor issues that might bother some people.  I\'m not bother by them a whole lot though. 1.  It takes somewhere between 5 and 10 minutes to brew.  I know  some people want it done faster but I just start it before I do anything else in the morning and that works for me.  I\'m not ready for coffee the second my feet hit the floor anyway. 2. It does tend to collect condensation around the outside.  A little annoying but I just make sure to wipe it up when I see it. 3. Some people also complained about the lack of an automatic shut off.  I kind of wish it had that feature but I guess the lack of it just makes me pay better attention to what I am doing.  Maybe that\'s not such a bad thing! 4. I haven\'t had too much trouble with it dripping coffee on the hot plate as some reviewers noted.  Maybe they\'re trying to pull the pot away before it is totally done dripping? Every coffee maker I\'ve ever had requires a moment or two for the last couple of drips to stop.  Any drips I do get I mop up right away and my hot plate looks fine. 5. The pot does get a little messy when you pour. I\'ve had that problem with other coffee makers too.  I\'ve learned to avoid a mess simply by pouring over the sink and then wiping off the pot with the dish cloth.  Problem solved. Overall I\'m happy with this coffee maker.  It does what I need it to do and performs as well as can be expected for a $15 machine.'),
(2975, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'New system I\'ve only had this brewer for a few weeks but it was very easy to set up and get going. The only complaint was there were no instructions for putting the charcoal water filter together. I bought a permenent brew basket at Bed Bath and Beyond at the same time and it works great in this brewing system. My daughter is using it right now while she is hear and is enjoying the pods that came with it. Fast and convenient to make coffee. Would have liked a permanent brew basket to be included with it instead of buying one separately.'),
(2976, 5, 1, 1, '2016-11-11', 'bah hunbug Machine quite working 3 months after purchase  can I return it for a new one?.'),
(2977, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-09', 'Five Stars Great'),
(2978, 9, 1, 1, '2016-08-21', 'Not a quality item. Began leaking within 4 months. A brew basket was replaced and one week later it began to leak again.  I contacted Cuisinart Customer Service and explained that the problem had occurred again only one week after the replacement part was put into use. I asked if there was are design defect and she did not know of one.  A whole new coffee maker is being sent at a cost to me of $10.00 and I have to send the old one back at my own expense. I am very disappointed with the quality of this Cuisanart Product. I expect Cuisinart products to be made better.  JJ.'),
(2979, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-25', 'Good for the money The blender meets my expectations for an inexpensive blender. It does the job, but with frozen fruit for smoothies, I do find myself opening and stirring a couple times, to help the blender get everything processed. Which is annoying, but I\'d rather do that than spend a couple hundred dollars on a blender. Everything can go in the dishwasher which is great.'),
(2980, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-19', 'Five Stars Perfect, Love everything about it.'),
(2981, 6, 1, 4, '2015-04-19', 'Four Stars Light weight and fast'),
(2982, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-07', 'Three Stars Does what it\'s supposed to do .... Nothing fancy'),
(2983, 3, 1, 3, '2015-04-07', 'Looking sharp It does the job very well I just don\'t like the part that it heats up around it on the  outside so much that I have to take everything away Only on one side of it stays cool'),
(2984, 4, 1, 5, '2016-03-21', 'One of my best purchases... One of my best purchases.  Bought it as a reconditioned model.  Still going strong after more than a year.  Heats quickly, cooks well.  I\'ve made cakes, pies, meat, etc.  Fish sticks nice nice and brown and crisp.'),
(2985, 8, 1, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Five Stars does the job'),
(2986, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-17', 'this is so efficient Great coffee machine. It get our coffee ready as we prepare to get to work, this is so efficient'),
(2987, 2, 1, 1, '2015-05-16', 'FIRE! This is the worst toaster oven I have ever operated! I\'ve only had it for a month and it has burned nearly all the food items I have put into it and caught three things on FIRE!!! Bagel, sliced bread, and a thick whole wheat tortilla all went up in flames on different occasions, regardless of proper control settings... I owned a Cuisinart TOB-40 for three years prior to this Black & Decker and never had problems. The only reason I had to replace it was because the door hinge broke off, otherwise, the heating elements worked great. I just bought another TOB-40 today to replace the B&D piece of crap. Too bad I am just a few days shy of the return policy. It is a FIRE HAZARD and should RECALLED by the manufacturer!'),
(2988, 7, 3, 1, '2016-06-29', 'I bought this Hamilton Beach and returned it for full refund at Walmart because it quit working after a couple of weeks. Water would boil but not drip or partially fill the cup. Took a chance on a second one thinking nothing could be that bad, but after several months it stopped working also. I only used pods so there was no coffee grounds to get stuck. I cleaned it out with a paper click just in case but, that was not the problem. I have read that Mr. Coffee has the same problems. I would not buy either one of them again. It really is as bad as people say. I imagine that the positive reviews are from people whose coffee maker is fairly new and has not yet gone out, but it will!'),
(2989, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'Five Stars son loved it and has put it to use, thanks for the great deal on it also'),
(2990, 5, 1, 1, '2016-10-10', 'Poor Quality.  Initial purchase and replacement shipped broken. I purchased this a few weeks back and it arrived with the front face plate broken off, like others have reported.  My replacement came today and it also arrived with the front face plate broken off.  I believe this is probably a defect since many others have reported the same issue.  I do not recommend and can\'t comment on coffee brewing abilities since I never plugged either of them in.'),
(2991, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-08', 'Good coffee maker! Works really well and keeps coffee hot.  Had a plastic filter from previous machine otherwise would have had to buy one.'),
(2992, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-15', 'Love it I like these so much I have one at work, one at home, and gave this one as a gift.  I add water first, then smoothie mix, frozen fruit and/or ice, then a little more water.  Blends perfectly.'),
(2993, 8, 1, 1, '2014-12-16', 'Stop producing garbage that pollutes the planet Stopped working after only 6 months.  Held together by non-standard screws to hinder repair. Dear Black and Decker, Please stop.  Stop producing such poorly made garbage. Please stop building products that are meant to fail after a short period of time. You are a disgrace to the universe.  Please stop.'),
(2994, 12, 1, 4, '2016-08-07', 'Don\'t turn on the oven and go about your business Okay, I like the thing. It has one flaw, however. When using the oven part, sometimes the light goes on and off. In order to keep the light on, you may have to push the toaster lever all the way to the left, again and again. It will stay on after a few tries, but do not turn on the oven and then go about your business. You may come back and find that the over never really came on all the way. Other than that, this is a good appliance. Fits nicely on the counter, is relatively attractive enough not to look like an eyesore, and works well.'),
(2995, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-23', 'Four Stars Works as well as most all the big blenders we\'ve had and a lot easier to clean'),
(2996, 4, 1, 2, '2016-02-01', 'toaster rack, in product start guide and on web ... toaster rack,in product  start guide and on web sites,pictures have small toast support wires welded to top of sliding frame.,item recieved location of the wires are on the bottom,making it difficult to slide the toast off of the rack. It has to be removed from the  rack with chopsticks or tongs! I returned another model of toaster oven for this reason,just want the model of toaster rack as pictured in the Cruisinart instruction and recipe booklet. Please send me the advertized  oven rack pictured on page 4 item 6 in the booklet.'),
(2997, 9, 1, 1, '2016-01-14', 'It leaks! We bought the 3000 for the ease of being able to pour right into the cup. It was great at first, the short cord is obnoxious but we still liked the machine. After a year, it started to leak. A lot. Faulty hoses and customer service can be compared to Comcast\'s. Yup. Don\'t bother buying this model.'),
(2998, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-11', 'Five Stars perfect toast'),
(2999, 2, 1, 4, '2016-06-22', 'Good price. Decent product. For the price this is a good toaster oven. It gets super hot and doesn\'t always toast evenly, but it does the job good enough for me.'),
(3000, 7, 3, 1, '2015-12-14', 'I bought the flex brew 6 weeks ago. It does not brew a decent cup of coffee if you use ground coffee. 2 days ago only a quarter of the water came out into the cup. Now the pump no longer works. We bought our Flex Brew at Home Hardware because it was cheaper than Walmart. I will definitely be looking for a Keurig to replace it.'),
(3001, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-24', 'Toaster and oven I love using this small toaster and countertop oven! Plus it looks adorable in my kitchen!.'),
(3002, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-28', 'We\'ve been using it for over 6 weeks now and are very happy with it Our son and wife gave us this coffee maker for Christmas.  We\'ve been using it for over 6 weeks now and are very happy with it. Pros: --Great  coffee flavor --I love the detachable water reservoir to fill.  This is really handy if we\'re drinking coffeee and just need to make a little extra to add to the pot.  --Programmable:  I set it up for each morning.  --Swing out coffee basket:  so  much easier to use. --Attractive and fits nicely under the counter.  Some other units are so large.  Cons: --I wish the carafe lid snapped around the rim of the carafe.  Sometimes if I\'m near the end of the pot and have to turn over the pot to pour, the   lid opens. --I wish it brewed a little more quickly. However, I\'ve had several other coffee makers, some more expensive, and this one makes the best coffee so far.'),
(3003, 4, 1, 4, '2015-06-05', 'Four Stars It\'s rather large for my Postage-Stamp Kitchen, but I move things out of the room.'),
(3004, 4, 1, 1, '2017-01-21', '5 alarm bell is ear-piercing just to alert toast is ready. Buyer beware Terrible toast beep that sounds like a high-pitched fire alarm. No way to disable beeping and wakes up the household if you use when people are sleeping. Just bought this last week but threw out box so instead of returning, we are throwing it out. Waste of $$ if you can\'t stand ridiculous alarm bell sounds for mere toast.'),
(3005, 4, 1, 1, '2016-03-11', 'bottom element dies after 22 months bought apr 2014.  Mar 2016 the lower element stopped working.  this is not acceptable for a $75 toaster oven branded Cuisnart....  Their products are usually much better.  the brand is why we bought his unit.'),
(3006, 1, 1, 1, '2016-09-22', 'Thanks for the defective machine! Amazon sent me a defective one or a refurbished one that doesn\'t work. First thing I noticed is that Amazon has sent me this machine in a big brown box. No damage or punctures on it. When I opened the box, there was another brown box which says it\'s the Keurig K250. So I opened that one and there was the actual Keurig box. But I noticed that the Keurig box was damaged on the top. I thought it was weird but I opened it up and everything was in there. I didn\'t notice anything damaged on the Keurig so I began to set everything up. I filled the reservoir to the minimum line just like the instruction booklet says. I turn on my Keurig K250 and it\'s going through some sort of process where it\'s taking in water. Seems normal right? Then it goes to a screen saying \"pre-heating\" and after 3 minutes, it says \"lift to begin\". Everything seems to be going alright. The booklet says to lift the handle all the way and bring it back down without a K-Cup Pod and it will give you an option to pour some hot water into a cup. This is where it went wrong. The screen is stuck on \"lift to begin\". Weird. So I re-did everything and it\'s still stuck. I look online for possible solutions but they all say to either call Keurig customer service or take it apart. I went with option 1 and called them. The customer service was super nice and we went through the whole situation. The lady told me that she is going to send me a new Keurig straight from them but it\'s going to take 3-7 business days. I don\'t mind the wait, but what I mind is why is Amazon sending defective items? Do they even check the product before they send it? Do they think refurbished is the new type of new? I\'m just furious that I can\'t have a cup of coffee before I go into work.'),
(3007, 7, 3, 1, '2016-03-03', 'Because you get what you pay for. I was pleased the first week. I even recommended to a fellow co-worker. I used exactly 8 coffee singles and it would not brew. I followed the instructions in the manual to clean and guess what? The manual provided is not the one for the flex brew. It is for a standard coffee maker. I went on line to see how to trouble shoot and followed the instructions. Of course, I did not save my instructions nor the box as I have limited space. I have called customer service and as of yet I have not received a return call. When working I LOVED it. I could start my coffee, prepare my vitamins and it was done. I was very happy and actually preferred over the famous keurig for a few days. If, Hamilton Beach responds and replaces this malfunctioning flex brew coffee maker I will give another review or amend this one. So disappointed'),
(3008, 9, 1, 1, '2016-03-12', 'Power cord is ridiculously short. The power cord is not even 2 inches long. It can\'t reach the electrical socket. The instructions claim that it\'s so short so that you don\'t trip over it. Really? Who walks on top of their kitchen counters or runs a coffee maker on the floor? This is my third one of these and I am returning it. The first 2 had normal power cords.'),
(3009, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-10', 'We chose this product as a supplement to our K-cup coffee maker, the original, because was having minor problems with the old one. Never expected the Hamilton Beach coffee maker to actually replace our old one but we haven\'t used it since. This coffee maker has some great features. Choosing between 6, 8, or 10 ounce cup is simple with the integrated measuring reservoir. I think it\'s a good thing this maker does not have an internal water holding tank, using only the amount of water poured in for that particular cup being made at that moment. I believe any water holding reservoir type of brewer has the potential of mold. I refer to that type of brewing as replacement through displacement. This Hamilton Beach eliminates that possibility. It\'s fast too. By the time I get done adding creamer, sweetener, and a little evaporated milk to a freshly made cup, another cup is done brewing too. The choice of regular and bold brew is another feature we really like. Initially I thought maybe the difference between the two modes might be temperature but it turns out to be how the water is introduced into the K-cup or brewing basket with whatever your choice of ground coffee. The regular brewing mode continuously pushes the water through as with any K-cup brewer but what\'s different with bold mode is it will momentarily pause intermittently through most of the brew process. It really does make a difference too. My wife likes the regular brew mode and I like the bold mode. Wish we discovered this FlexBrew a long time ago.'),
(3010, 6, 1, 1, '2014-12-18', 'Cooks unevenly.  Not typical Cuisinart Quality by a long shot. Ugh...Cooks unevenly. Clearly this is a product that purchased the licence to use the cuisinart name.'),
(3011, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Good quality and value Great toaster. Looks great. Easy to use. Can cook anything in this thing. Nice value.'),
(3012, 4, 1, 4, '2015-08-11', 'Four Stars Easy to use controls. Toaster cooks toast as set by the controls.'),
(3013, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-01', 'Compact design, consistent coffee and easy to clean! I\'ve had this coffee maker for a couple months and I still love it. I originally purchased this model because of the compact design (thin but tall) which allowed me to have a regular size coffee pot without losing counter space. It also offers programs like 1-4 cups, which I use daily, or multiple cups for company (or the serious coffee addict). What I didn\'t expect to like about this product was how easy it is to clean. I purchased, separately, the reusable coffee filter (shown in pictures) because producing less waste is important to me. You do have to turn the coffee pot upside down to get the last couple tablespoons of coffee out, but I don\'t drink that anyways (I find there\'s always a little bit of silt in the last couple tablespoons anyways). Turning it upside down is a little annoying, but it cleans really easily otherwise. The coffee is consistent and delicious. I\'ve used it almost every day. I did a lot of research on the other options for coffee makers but ultimately chose this for the slim design, programmable options and clock display. If these are important to you, then this product is the best you can do.'),
(3014, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'Love it Awesome toaster works great!'),
(3015, 7, 3, 5, '2016-02-21', 'Purchased the coffee maker 3 weeks ago.I have used it everyday.It\'s a lovely machine,coffee is nice and hot and the price was a real treat.'),
(3016, 4, 1, 5, '2016-09-21', 'Great gift and very easy to use!! Awesome purchased for my 94 yr old grandma. She was able to use it with no problem at all very intuitive and easy to use..'),
(3017, 6, 1, 1, '2015-09-15', 'Cuisinart is going downhill. We had a Cuisinart toaster for many years which was excellent.  When part of the heating elements stopped working, I bought this one because the original model had been discontinued.  This one I received did not work properly.  Only one side of the bread was brown, but the other side was barely warm.  (It was the toast setting, and not the bagel setting.)  I returned it.'),
(3018, 5, 1, 3, '2015-08-22', 'Overrated The high reviews for this product seem unwarranted, unless people are factoring in the low price. If people are being honest, it\'s not a 5-star product. I measured the water temperature where it hits the coffee, and only got 181 degrees F. Optimal temp to extract coffee flavor is around 200 degrees, so it\'s not even close. Other issues: - You can\'t pour out the last drops from the carafe, which makes emptying and cleaning difficult. Some reviewers say this is a positive so they don\'t spill coffee from a full pot or have drips, but that\'s never been a problem for me. - It has acres of black plastic and not as much stainless as the front picture shows, but that\'s expected at this price range. - The blue clock light is incredibly bright at night. Positives include that it allows for a bolder setting and there is no annoying beeping like some competing models.'),
(3019, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-25', 'Five Stars Works like advertised. Perfectly satisfied.'),
(3020, 2, 1, 2, '2015-05-11', 'Two Stars Sending back as it is too large for the space I have to put it in.'),
(3021, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-09', 'If I designed a coffemaker this would be it! Love love love this!  I LOVE the removable water reservoir -- convenient to fill and clean!  The basket swings out and removes without a plastic lip underneath which gets gross.  The carafe is generous and doesn\'t spill while pouring.  When you remove the carafe it does not drip.  The programming is great.  You have regular, 1-4 cup (light), or bold brews.  There is a timer.  You can turn down the hot plate temp. so it doesn\'t cook and get bitter.  LOVE this coffeemaker after years of the standard-issue Mr. Coffee.'),
(3022, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-15', 'Five Stars Best cheap coffee maker on the market.  Works flawlessly after 4 months of use.'),
(3023, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-08', 'This Toaststation is amazing! It\'s well built and the perfect size This Toaststation is amazing! It\'s well built and the perfect size. It toast fast and evenly, not to mention it\'s super cute! I love this guy!'),
(3024, 3, 1, 4, '2016-06-07', 'Good toaster oven. It took me a few times to get the new smell out. It did have a small scratch ontop but I don\'t think its something to have to send it back. But the price it costs it should have been handled better. I hope the pics help. *I have not contacted the seller about this.'),
(3025, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-05', 'Five Stars 1'),
(3026, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-13', 'Older Model - Don\'t Wash Tray in Dishwasher! So far this has been a good toaster oven.  I haven\'t put it through all the paces, however, I did make a good grilled cheese the other day.  It\'s a  nice size for my small countertops and did not get broiling hot on top as my older model did.  It really makes an annoying ticking sound like an old-fashioned oven timer while it cycles through the cooking time.  I don\'t know if I could deal with that for a full 30 minutes if I were to bake something.  I stuck the cheesy pan in the dishwasher after its first use and pulled it out after cleaning only to discover it was a dull gray color and the finish was streaking off with a black dust on my hands.  I threw it out immediately and checked the B&D site for a replacement.  Holy cow - the shipping is more than the cost of the pan!  I also discovered that parts for this model are obsolete.  I\'ve found a replacement pan on Amazon that is a good size for this (check your sizes - this is a smaller oven).  I will update more shortly.  If I didn\'t throw away the box, I probably would\'ve returned this and researched a newer model at a big box before I purchased this again.  Lesson learned.'),
(3027, 5, 1, 3, '2015-05-12', 'Water Drips out I\'ve had this for a few months now and it\'s leaking somehow all over the burner and brewing only half of what I put in.  I\'m trying to fix it, but no luck yet.  It\'s a nice coffee maker otherwise.'),
(3028, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-05', 'Good for single use I have used every morning for 1 month. It works well. Reasonable price. Good for single use.'),
(3029, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-11', 'Four Stars Great for a quick smoothie, but leaves ice pieces in the beverage. I would buy it again.'),
(3030, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-18', 'I Love this coffee pot I Love this coffee pot !!!!!!  If your looking for a coffee pot this is the one to purchase.. Has many nice feature\'s to it, You can remove the back and take it to the sink to fill the water, or you can use the pot. The basket has a button that poop\'s the basket out, It rolls out from under cabinets, has wonderful LED lighting, will make 1-4 cups of coffee at the push of a button, I really can\'t say enough about this coffee pot. If your looking for a coffee pot, This one will not disappoint you !!!!!'),
(3031, 5, 1, 4, '2014-03-20', 'Excellent Flavor I am very happy with my purchase.  The coffee maker is very easy to use and works perfectly.  I love the Bold Brew option. The coffee tastes great!  The only downside (and the reason I didn\'t give this unit 5 stars) was when I brewed a 4 cup pot I didn\'t feel that the coffee had an opportunity to get hot enough because it didn\'t sit on the burner long enough.'),
(3032, 4, 1, 3, '2015-02-16', 'A good toaster oven. Needs a built in timer for other functions besides just \"toast\". Not having a built in timer when on the \"bake\" function is annoying. Also the beeping noise it makes when it\'s done toasting is loud and sounds almost like a smoke detector. Other than these couple gripes, it\'s a perfectly good toaster oven that get the job done well enough.'),
(3033, 9, 1, 1, '2015-07-10', 'Grounds in the coffee and everywhere else! This coffee pot doesn\'t have a problem making coffee....the problem it has is keeping the grounds out of the coffee cup once dispensed.  I\'ve contact the maker and have had no response yet. And lastly the ground bubble up during the perk process and stick to the shower head which requires major cleaning after each pot.'),
(3034, 9, 1, 4, '2015-03-20', 'Good coffee from a good maker This coffee maker is better than I hoped for. It\'s easy to clean. I like all the features; they\'re really useful.'),
(3035, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'Five Stars Great value, all the features of the more expensive units!'),
(3036, 8, 1, 1, '2016-04-07', 'One Star Only worked for 6 months and it stopped working today, doesn\'t get hot.'),
(3037, 2, 1, 3, '2015-08-31', 'Three Stars It is really small.  Buy a bigger one.'),
(3038, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Great and easy to us Great and easy to us. I haven\'t tried blending up more than some easy shakes and sauces, but it works great so far!'),
(3039, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-27', 'Five Stars I am very pleased with my  mini blender. For the price it does a really good job!!'),
(3040, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-30', 'Everything I could have asked for! It\'s powerful, ... Everything I could have asked for! It\'s powerful, simple and stores well. Most importantly, it has no problem crushing ice.'),
(3041, 12, 1, 1, '2014-11-05', 'It breaks! The door of the mini oven broke when I temped to use it for the first time. I have been using the toaster and it worked great until the door incident. Now the door doesn\'t close so I can not use it as a toaster.'),
(3042, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-10', 'perfect for our teen and us :) I love the tasty variety of grilled sandwiches we can make as well as warming up leftover taquitos or pizza. And toast is done in seconds !my family loves it!'),
(3043, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-23', 'I like the crumb tray This was just as expected. I like the crumb tray. The only possible complaint I might have is the knob for making toast is a bit difficult to control.'),
(3044, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-10', 'Great Hot Coffee Every Day Loving the \"Hamilton Beach 46201 12 Cup Digital Coffeemaker, Stainless Steel \".  Use it every day for the past 5 months I\'ve had it.  Couldn\'t be easier to use and clean. Makes great hot coffee and keeps it hot.  With automatically shut off in 2 hours if you forget and leave it on. Easy to program the night before for next morning coffee. Doesn\'t take up much space on counter top. Highly recommend this one.'),
(3045, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'awesome this is the best cup of coffee that I have made at home , ever.  love the pull out basket and rotating base.  I have my pot set on bold strength and it is perfect.  this pot replaced one that was one month old (hate it).'),
(3046, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'Good little coffee pot! I am happy with this machine.  It is easy to load and put water in and makes good coffee.  It is a good size for the counter top and with the pot tucked inside the machine there is much less risk of breakage.'),
(3047, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-02', 'Worth every penny Fantastic!!!'),
(3048, 6, 1, 1, '2016-02-22', 'It has a mind of it\'s own as far as how dark to toast my favorite bread. I use the same brand and variety ... I have been using Cuisinart appliances for many years and I must say that this toaster is not worth a darn. It has a mind of it\'s own as far as how dark to toast my favorite bread. I use the same brand and variety of bread all the time, sometimes it\'s burned and sometimes it\'s too light, and once in a while it\'s just right, and no I don\'t change the setting. Will not buy another toaster from Cuisinart!'),
(3049, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-19', 'Melted knob... Dont buy. Timer knob melted til it simply spun on its shaft. Took the knob off... Split in two pieces, and melted. Oven was on 400 for 1 hour and 20 minutes... Was using the Leave-on feature... Fire hazzard imo. Purchased in June 2016. Unless this oven is proven to be fixed... Ill not buy another...and cant reccomend this model.  STAY CLEAR!.'),
(3050, 5, 1, 2, '2016-07-24', 'Two Stars Very cheap!'),
(3051, 4, 1, 3, '2016-02-04', 'Unsafe, power flickers on/off The toaster is great, BUT, it seems to flicker power on and off, which is really not safe at all and it is really not cool to have to plug in and unplug with each use.  So, I\'m not really satisfied with that.  But as for how it bakes and toasts, I have been satisfied....until the house burns down one day when we forget to unplug it.... It flickers on and off when the top dial is in the \"Off\" position.....it also flickers on and off when it is in the \"toast\" position with the timer at 0 and toaster off.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(3052, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-13', 'Very Good Cooks evenly and I love the timer that will shut it off should I forget...not all of the ones I tried had a timer.  Great value for the price. I would have given it 5-stars if the tray would have slid out when the door was opened....it\'s a hassle to have to grab a pot holder, etc. Also, I do not think 4 slices will fit at the same time, unless they were smaller than average bread slices.'),
(3053, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-09', 'I love this Hamilton beach coffee maker the ease of confeniance ... I have been drinking coffee for fifty years  so you know I have went thru a lot of different coffee pots including the bunn that is a #1 seller ! I love this  Hamilton beach coffee maker the ease of confeniance  easy to clean and the little wheels on the bottom make it easy to move and the coffee tasts good too !  the bunn did every thing it said it would BUT the cleaning left a lot to be desired the holding tank in witch the water is stored hot for your next pot of coffee can not be cleaned right no matter how much cleaning you put it thru I found out that it builds up a green and black mossy substance inside of the tank that will not come out with vinegar or any cleaner no matter what you use  !  i\'ll keep my Hamilton beach it comes apart very easy and you know you got it clean simple'),
(3054, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'Five Stars Great looking toaster, works great too. Just remember to turn it off if you are using the oven feature.'),
(3055, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-25', 'Very good coffee maker Makes good coffee and hold the coffee hot enough.'),
(3056, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-14', 'This is a great little smoothie maker for work This is a great little smoothie maker for work.  I use it everyday to make my morning smoothies. It is easy to clean and it is compact enough to fit in my desk drawer. The only think I don\'t like about it is that the cord is really short. Since I am not using on a kitchen counter I have to plug it in to an outlet along the back wall in my office and hold the blender. It\'s not a big deal, but I wish the cord was longer.'),
(3057, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-17', 'Does what its supposed to do but the timer seems ... Does what its supposed to do but the timer seems hard to retract thus once you set you cant go back!'),
(3058, 8, 1, 5, '2014-11-10', 'Hot Coffee Yes I like to keep going back to the pot, this machine keeps it Hot! Plus it looks sleek, love it.'),
(3059, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-09', 'A great toaster! A great toaster! I just replaced my 5 year old toaster because I\'m changing the kitchen color scheme to a basic white. My older, orange colored toaster was much more expensive, and yet this one toasts the bread quicker and much more evenly. I was pleasantly surprised. Cuisinart is a well trusted brand for a good reason. Their appliances work great!'),
(3060, 9, 1, 4, '2015-06-03', 'Nice design, fun to have the \"fuel tank\" to ... Nice design, fun to have the \"fuel tank\" to show how much is left.  Coffee tastes fine.  I have two comments about this machine.  The cord seems to be really short.  After contacting Cuisinart about it, they said it is 28\" long--we were seeing only about 14\".  We pulled REALLY REALLY hard and got more out...but this is a stupid design, as most people would be afraid of breaking it by pulling so hard--we were.  Second, it goes from half full to empty really fast!--so probably not really an accurate gauge. We get about 5 to 5 1/2 good size coffee mugs out of a 12 cup (the maximum) setting.  Easy to clean.'),
(3061, 12, 1, 4, '2014-01-23', 'This is a great compact unit. This is the second Toastation Toaster Oven  I have owned.  The first one lasted for seven years of heavy use.  After seven years it still worked, but it no longer seemed to get as hot as it should. What I like best is the compact size of having two appliances in one.  I feel a top load toaster toasts more evenly than putting toast on the rack of a toaster oven.  One big improvement on this model is that you can push a button to make the toast pop.  In the older model (which is still available)  you had to unplug the toaster to make it pop up if you wanted to pop it up before the toaster thought it was finished.  Dumb design.  Another improvement on this model is that they repositioned the dials so that the toaster dial is on top and the other dial is below it.  That just makes sense to me, but on the older model these were reversed.  Lastly, I like having the option of the red enamel on the front, particularly because it is easier to keep clean than the stainless steel in my opinion.. I wish I could give this toaster oven 4.5 stars.  I wish they made this toaster oven available in a slightly larger size  .  Specifically, I wish it were a little bit taller.  My husband and I use the oven part often to heat things like pizza slices and sandwiches.  If the interior of the oven was a little taller  I think I would use it even more.  That\'s the only reason I didn\'t give this five stars.'),
(3062, 2, 1, 1, '2015-04-23', 'flimsy flimsy'),
(3063, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-23', 'Makes hot coffee I like it. It is small which is good since I don\'t have a lot of counter space for it. It brews slowly, but maybe that\'s a good thing? If it brewed too quickly maybe it wouldn\'t pick up as much of the coffee flavor. Either way, this coffeemaker keeps the liquid hot. I have a wonderful husband who starts my coffee before I get up. If I am having a lazy morning and it takes me a while to wake up, the coffee is still hot when I get to it.'),
(3064, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'Love this toaster oven.convection oven! Great toaster oven/convection oven!  Toasts great with a bunch of settings.  Its a nice size and a lot of my dishes fit in here. Love the oven function as my kitchen is small so this gives me another oven for the holidays for small dishes.'),
(3065, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-18', 'Great coffee pot!! This IS the best coffee maker we\'ve ever owned.  It brews the best tasting coffee.  The pour spout is really drip-free... no coffee on the counter.  Clean-up is easy as well as the programming.  The only thing I don\'t care for is the lid to the pot fits very tightly in the grooves which makes it difficult to put back on after cleaning.'),
(3066, 3, 1, 4, '2016-09-17', 'Great toaster oven Great toaster oven. We use this frequently and have had zero issues. Yes it gets hot on the outside when using it, it\'s an oven, it\'s supposed to. People complaining about the heat it omits need to be banned from reproducing. Frozen food, veggies, homemade pizza, chicken, brownies... everything has worked well. My only complaint and it\'s a small one is that the alert tone is not loud enough.'),
(3067, 9, 1, 2, '2016-05-17', 'I like this coffee maker but as of last week I like this coffee maker but as of last week, once I pour the first cup, the machine keeps dripping coffee until the whole thing is empty. I have only had this machine for six months and I need to replace it. Very disappointed.'),
(3068, 1, 1, 4, '2015-09-12', 'I like the Keurig 250 for brewing quick cup of coffee and the color sandy pearl matches the kitchen decor. However..... Large foot print on my counter top.  No on/off switch.'),
(3069, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-01', 'Great product Makes better tasting coffee than my last coffee pot. What more can I ask for?'),
(3070, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-13', 'Great product for the price I had bought a toaster few years back for double the price that was half as good. Have had it for month and I love it. Cannot believe what a good deal it was'),
(3071, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-06', 'Five Stars Love it.'),
(3072, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'Great oven for the price!! This was a replacement for my old B & D Toaster oven. What a great product this is. Love my 12\" pizzas cooked in this. Toaster a little slow but as expected. Highly recommend this one for the money.'),
(3073, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'So far we are very happy with this new toaster So far we are very happy with this new  toaster; it does 4 slices at a time and browns evenly.'),
(3074, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-04', 'Love my Cuisinart coffee maker!!! Makes great coffee! There\'s no carafe to break, and I love the way it dispenses coffee, one cup at a time. It\'s pretty easy to clean, too!  It\'s also a very nice looking coffee maker!  So glad I decided to make this purchase!!!'),
(3075, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-28', 'Best Coffee Pot Ever! We love this coffee pot...we had one years ago and it got fried in an electrical storm.  Tried a cheaper version and finally went back an bought this again.'),
(3076, 2, 1, 3, '2015-12-09', 'So far, so good Pretty good for the price, but has a few problems.  Like every other cheap toaster oven I\'ve had, the temperature doesn\'t not stay constant ...making it pretty useless for actually cooking something. For toasting and warming, it works pretty well.  Toast will usually be browner on the bottom, with an uneven grill looking pattern. The thing that confounds me are the labels on the dials.  Defying all laws of physics and common sense, \"broil\" and \"toast\" are shown as temperatures and cooking modes on both dials.  So, your temperature could be \"toast\", but you could still have it on \"bake\" on the mode dial ... meaning you are baking at the highest temp.  You could also \"broil\" (a lower temperature) with both burners on.  It\'s just goofy and un-American.  Why not just use all numbers on the temp dial, and simple upper, bottom or both burner settings on the other dial.'),
(3077, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Five Stars Works even better thatn I thought, crushed Ice, frozen fruit. Just need to pulse it.'),
(3078, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-25', 'Five Stars Loved this!'),
(3079, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'I love this blender I love this blender! I make smoothies with it and it\'s the perfect size, nice and small and fits on my small amount of counter space. I tend to blend frozen fruit in my smoothies and it blends it finely. I haven\'t blended ice in it, so I\'m not sure about that, I think it would blend it, I\'ve never had any large pieces of fruit in my drinks.'),
(3080, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'Good toasting Works great--hope it lasts longer than the other-brand toaster did.'),
(3081, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Good product Very high quality and works amazing. Never had a single issue with this product at all. Would recommend to anyone who is looking for a toaster oven.'),
(3082, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-03', 'works great. arrived fast. works great.'),
(3083, 7, 3, 5, '2014-08-25', 'It worked perfectly and was the right size for taking camping.'),
(3084, 11, 1, 4, '2014-07-20', 'Four Stars Great toaster for the price. Too bad the power-cord is a little short.'),
(3085, 7, 3, 2, '2016-09-25', 'Do not purchase if the majority of your coffee comes from K-Cups. Works fine with the coffee filter basket and hotel single brew filters. I only get about a half cup of coffee when using K-Cups and too many coffee grinds. I\'m going to return to get a Keurig.'),
(3086, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-19', 'Love it and the $$ I can\'t believe how affordable this thing was & how well it performs with no issues. Was def worth the buy _'),
(3087, 8, 1, 4, '2014-02-28', 'Just the right size 5-cup is just the right size for us, and I wanted to replace a white model that was starting to show its age. The only complaint I have is that there is not a drip pause on this pot. I didn\'t think to look for that in my search, so that\'s my fault. Otherwise, I really like this pot, particularly the all-black color.  The drip issue isn\'t really a problem since it only makes 5 cups.  I was just surprised when I brewed the first pot.'),
(3088, 8, 1, 5, '2015-07-05', 'Five Stars Great for 2 people works great!'),
(3089, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Love this coffeemaker! I use it daily and can say that this is my favorite coffee maker out of all I\'ve ever owned.'),
(3090, 5, 1, 2, '2016-07-18', 'Not even worth it. I could never get this thing to brew the coffee at a hot enough temperature. I\'m not talking like ridiculous hot, I\'m just talking about normal coffee temperature hot. The coffee also always came away with a weird taste. I should have returned this but foolishly thought I could fix it or that the low temp and bad taste were things that would get better. They did not. I use a french press now and this thing sits on my counter top just because it has a clock on it.'),
(3091, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-11', 'A perfect toaster oven. Searching for the perfect toaster oven with good reviews and a decent price, this one was the lucky winner! Toasts perfectly and evenly, has many functions and a good size. Exactly what I had been looking for!'),
(3092, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-29', 'Wonderful Product! Love my new toaster oven!! It has made cooking smaller items simple. Definitely would recommend buying this.'),
(3093, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-22', 'Recommend without hesitation Tried a lot of coffee pots.  I insist on a removable reservoir and this one is one of the best I\'ve had. 12 cup capacity a bonus.'),
(3094, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-26', 'This works good for someone who wants a cup of coffee. Now I plan to buy some tea kurig cups to brew too. I am pleased with my purchase.'),
(3095, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-25', 'Trust Me, Spend a Little More for a Better Blender Don\'t buy this blender. If you\'re looking at this product, you\'re most likely in need of a small portable blender but don\'t want to spend a lot of money. My advice: spend more money for a higher quality product. The lid on this blender is nowhere near secure. You\'ll have to use napkins or paper towels every time you use it. It\'s a mess, and on top of that, the lid broke after 5 uses. Note to Amazon: First off, I love Amazon. Buying products on this site is incredibly convenient and you gotta love Prime free shipping. However, I suggest you take these really low-quality products off your site. This one in particular is just a waste of money, and now I need to spend even more to buy a better blender.'),
(3096, 4, 1, 1, '2016-01-13', 'Don\'t Waste Your Money! I purchased this toaster oven a little over two years ago and it was always problematic. The settings were always inaccurate and we constantly had to deal with charred toast or soggy quesadillas. After about a year of use, one of the broiler burners began to \"droop\" down, exposing the red hot metal. It finally stopped working all together. Not a durable product! It is a lot more inexpensive than the other toaster ovens for a reason! I recommend spending a bit more and get a decent one!'),
(3097, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'Five Stars Superb brew!'),
(3098, 6, 1, 5, '2017-01-05', 'No arguement Excellent toaster, and should have purchased this long before now.'),
(3099, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-23', 'Awesome little Coffee Brewer This is the perfect size coffee maker for our RV! Love it'),
(3100, 4, 1, 3, '2016-01-11', 'Improvements don\'t always make it better I have owned Cuisinart products all my life and even bought this as a replacement for the same exact model I had for years. While Cuisinart made some changes that were really needed for this model, they fell short in meeting my expectations and made other changes that negatively affected it. They made improvements to the dials from the previous version, but the dials are black, with no indication of the dial point, other than they raised it. By doing so, you can hardly see where, or what function it is pointing at. The indicator point should be silver, or white. The slot for the oven rack has been moved and the oven rack has a more curved angle to it. This is also not a positive aspect, because it now it has the toast why too close to the top. And for what ever reason, it just simply does not toast as well as the older model. The last fault in this toaster is that the sound when the cycle has completed. It is so loud, it will wake up the house when it goes off and I am not kidding. NOT A GOOD FEATURE! The major improvement is that they went to an all aluminum coated interior. This is a vast improvement from the painted interior of the older model. The older model\'s painted interior started chipping/burning away after time. This new interior is much better in appearance and way better to clean. While I still think the toaster and oven is superior to the other brands on the market, I think Cuisinart took a step backwards and is letting the competition catch up.'),
(3101, 6, 1, 1, '2015-06-14', 'Don\'t Get Burned! This toaster burns the bread if set higher than level 2 (7 being the highest) and only toasts one side of the bread.'),
(3102, 12, 1, 4, '2015-11-07', 'Four Stars B'),
(3103, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-08', 'Five Stars good product'),
(3104, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-25', 'Five Stars great product.'),
(3105, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-27', 'Five Stars made a good cup of coffee ease of use.'),
(3106, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-09', 'Five Stars Excellent product'),
(3107, 9, 1, 1, '2016-05-26', 'Hope yours is better than my two. I owned the older model - the DCC2000.  It was fabulous and lasted 4 years until it began to not brew as hot as it did when we got it. Easy fix we think and we purchased the newer model, the DCC3000.  It brews at least 30 degrees cooler which means cold coffee when you add milk to your coffee.  Yes I checked with a thermometer.  No big deal.  I took it back to the store and they ordered me a replacement from their warehouse.  Same story only this one was cooler than the first.  What a bummer. This was a fabulous coffee maker and I don\'t know if this was just a bad lot to one company or the coffee maker is now really lousy.  I want my coffee hot out of the pot not lukewarm!'),
(3108, 5, 1, 1, '2016-02-26', 'After the first day that I purchased the coffee maker ... After the first day that I purchased the coffee maker, the face plate broke off. I sent it back and got a replacement and after 1 week of use, the face plate broke off again.'),
(3109, 2, 1, 2, '2016-02-06', 'which my husband is NOT happy about. The dials are just a little confusing ... Not real crazy about this toaster.  It\'s smaller than our previous one, which my husband is NOT happy about.  The dials are just a little confusing but it does work fine, just not our favorite toaster oven we\'ve ever had.'),
(3110, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-27', 'Great size. Got this for my son for Christmas.  Great size.'),
(3111, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-20', 'Easy to use and easy to clean. My wife and I so enjoy our original one that we got another as a back-up.'),
(3112, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-10', 'Five Stars It\'s my favorite toaster oven with a toaster. Great for a small kitchen with little counter space.'),
(3113, 5, 1, 3, '2015-09-28', 'Three Stars Kept as a back up.'),
(3114, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Very happy!! Very happy!!! The pot does not drip!!! We had a Braun and everytime we would pour a cup of coffee the darn thing would drip between the rim and the glass. NO issues with this one!!!'),
(3115, 3, 1, 4, '2015-01-20', 'Four Stars great products works like a charm'),
(3116, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-21', 'Useful I always make banana smoothie almost everyday.This Blender is very useful. It can grind 2x2 inch big ice cubes. Easy to clean. Inexpensive. Shipping was fast!'),
(3117, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-21', 'We weren\'t sure how well it would blend ice but it seems to work great so far Works really well! Bought this for my husband who makes shakes daily. We weren\'t sure how well it would blend ice but it seems to work great so far.'),
(3118, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-13', 'good toaster oven works exactly as described.  heats up quickly, very convenient to use'),
(3119, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-11', 'Five Stars its good'),
(3120, 6, 1, 2, '2016-12-04', 'Sadly, wouldn\'t recommend My husband & I purchased this item in June 2015 because of reviews and product brand is supposedly a good company. It does not get used daily so  I\'m very disappointed that after 1 year, it no longer works properly.  I purchased the 2-slice toaster.  Both slots only toast half the bread. We have to flip the bread a couple of time to get it toasted evenly and now after 1 1/2 years, it doesn\'t even do that.  Poor quality. Dissatisfied. Shame on Cuisinart.'),
(3121, 3, 1, 1, '2015-01-05', 'Got it today, and I am returning it tomorrow. Why they make products  like this??? I Got it today, and I am returning it tomorrow. The door drops as soon as you open it, there is no safety to hold the door close. The outside of the oven gets as hot as inside of it, you can cook an egg on top of it white cooking your pastries inside it. I burned my hand touching it, I am glad  it was me and not my kids. what is going on... Black and Decker got purchased by Chinese??? Shame on them.'),
(3122, 9, 1, 3, '2016-04-07', 'My second one is now $$$ down the drain My 2nd one is broken now too. Received my 1st as a gift and it lasted 4 years. My 2nd lasted 5 years. My gauge was not working properly after the 2nd year. I no longer could program it to brew as well. I loved it until all of these problems.'),
(3123, 1, 1, 4, '2015-07-01', 'A great Keurig machine! My husband has an older model of Keurig at work, and he had been wanting one at home. I was so pleased to find one in a color that would coordinate with our kitchen in a fun way! The machine itself is great -- we\'ve had no problems with it. I also love that we can purchase the carafe optionally and brew larger pots when company comes over. I have yet to figure out if you can purchase a refillable pod that works with this machine. That\'s one thing I want to find out about still, since the pods are quite expensive! They\'re cheaper than a Starbucks run, though, so we have that going for us. :) I have found that many of our travel mugs are too tall to fit in this machine. That\'s a bit of a bummer. Our Starbucks \"grande\" sized mug BARELY fits underneath, and taller mugs will not work. I was hopeful that removing the drip catcher on the bottom would allow me to use a taller mug, but it appears that this piece HAS to be in place for it to brew (it\'s the same place the carafe connects, so that you HAVE to use their carafe, not any other pot). My husband loves the flavor of the coffee and variety of pods available, so he\'s ultimately a happy camper! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3124, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-19', 'A good durable toaster oven. Basic, priced right and effective.'),
(3125, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-12', 'Fantastic so far. Great coffee pot!  I\'ve only had this for a week, so I will have to update in a few months because so many items are manufactured to fall apart in no time. This pot has a great design. The water reservoir lifts off or can be filled using your carafe. The carafe is designed with a strip of plastic across the carafe which keeps the pot from dripping everywhere when you fill your cup, a great design innovation. The chamber which holds the grounds snaps open and is convenient.  The pot isn\'t as tall as my old pot and has a slightly smaller footprint. My old pot cost quite a bit more and still quit after less than a year. So far, I love, love, love this one.'),
(3126, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-31', 'so I decided to go back to my Cuisinart and yes I love it I previously owned a Cuisinart and got rid of it and purchased a Kerig, but I ended up not liking it or the price of coffee K-cups, so I decided to go back to my Cuisinart and yes I love it'),
(3127, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Best blender ever___ Best blender ever___'),
(3128, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-28', 'Solid product, but does NOT fit a 9\" round pizza This is a good, reliable product. But please note: it does NOT fit a 9\" round pizza. It fits a 9\"x5\" rectangular pizza. They really should not claim it fits a 9\" pizza. Also, just a word of warning...the instructions explicitly state that you cannot use aluminum foil in the toaster oven. That means you need to clean the tray meticulously after every use (instead of just tossing the sheet of aluminum foil). So if those things are OK with you, then you\'re good to go. It does cook small pizzas beautifully. And it\'s a good price.'),
(3129, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-23', 'Overall, glad I ditched the Keurig... I ditched the Keurig in light of all the recent noise about the dangers of heating the K-cup plastics and then drinking liquid funneled through them. After doing a LOT of research on which coffee pot would have the least amount of dangerous plastic components, I settled in this one. The lid and the reservoir are plastic, (BPA-free) according to their website, but the carafe is of course, glass. I do miss the convenience of the Keurig, but this machine is super-easy to use and brews quickly and quietly. We can set it to have a pot brewed from us in the morning and the removable reservoir is what I was used to with the Keurig, so I love the ease of being able to pop that right out and carry it over to the sink.'),
(3130, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-02', 'Great product for a ridiculous price I had the previous version of this exact same toaster and frankly for such an inexpensive item it has been doing a great job for quite a few years (until I dropped it and it stopped working, couldn\'t blame it for that). This new version is even better:  works like a charm, I love the sleek and neat design this one has, plus there is now a reheating button which is actually quite useful.'),
(3131, 6, 1, 3, '2016-12-15', 'Three Stars Looks tinny sounds tinny, but it does the job.'),
(3132, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-13', 'Good coffee maker. Recommend the bold setting Bought this as a gift for my mom and she has raved a about it with out solicitation a couple times to me. She uses it on the bold setting and says it makes the best coffee she has had at home.'),
(3133, 10, 1, 2, '2015-04-18', 'takes forever Takes forever to blend _ but I like the size of it After a while of blending and failing I ate it like ice cream !'),
(3134, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-06', '... wood \" Been using for almost a year Does great Sounds like it will burn up since new \"Knock on wood \" Been using for almost a year Does great Sounds like it will burn up since new lol'),
(3135, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-29', 'Great personal blender for those personal protein shakes This personal blender works great. I\'ve been using other ones that I bought about 3 years ago that are still holding up. The clear plastic blender/cup is showing its age. A little \"foggy \",but no leaks and still work great.'),
(3136, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'Excellent coffee maker for the price! Excellent coffee maker for the price. Love the gage that tells you if there is still coffee in the reservoir.  Another great feature is the light that comes on when filling your cup; no more over filling. Have had the coffee maker for about a month now and haven\'t really found anything that I don\'t like about it. If I could change anything it would be to have a detachable lid in order to clean the water dispenser.'),
(3137, 5, 1, 2, '2016-03-21', '... tons of time in the AM and don\'t mind crappy coffee, this is the maker for you If you have tons of time in the AM and don\'t mind crappy coffee, this is the maker for you.  It takes 10-15 minutes to brew coffee! Also, the warming time is only 2 hours max.'),
(3138, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-22', 'Not powerful at all This product would probably be okay to make smoothies but the motor is not strong enough to do much else.  I bought this to have a separate small blender to make my daughters baby food, it doesnt work well for that at all.  It is not strong.  I will probably end up getting a magic bullet.'),
(3139, 1, 1, 1, '2016-07-04', 'Don\'t bother, look for an older model. Not a fan of the new features or the 3d bar codes.  The new 2.0 features completely take control away from me to make the cup of coffee I want the way I want it to taste.  I am actually sad I gave up my cheap $25 4 cup coffee maker for this thing.  I will be returning this immediately.  I\'m sad that Keurig went this route and broke what used to be a great product by adding \"improvements.\"'),
(3140, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'One person perfection for a personal blender! Love,  love, love this! Better than expected!'),
(3141, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-27', 'Definitely a big improvement over my previous coffee brewer!!! Just received the Cuisinart Coffee-on-Demand this week and my husband and I are thoroughly delighted with it.  First of all, there is no glass carafe needed.  Having the12 cup reservoir is convenient as well as easy to clean.  Just brew as much coffee as you like for your family in the AM and then have it accessible throughout the day.  This feature makes it extremely convenient also when you have guests who like more than one cup of coffee.  We are looking forward to enjoying our new coffee brewer for many years without having to worry about replacing a broken carafe!!!.'),
(3142, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-22', 'Very good'),
(3143, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-03', 'The standard-issue toaster oven does a standard-issue job. I ... The standard-issue toaster oven does a standard-issue job. I wish the power switch and the timer were separate so you could set the timer and then get the same time and toast level every time. Instead you have to carefully position the timer for every single use.'),
(3144, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', '5_ Do not regret this purchase! Love waking up to amazing coffee each morning! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3145, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-30', 'Nice small toaster oven for price Great little toaster oven for the price! This toaster oven is great for small food items and it toasts nicely.'),
(3146, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-17', 'Great for making shakes at work! This is no Vitamix, folks.  But it works.  Here\'s the short list: 1) You can put ice cubes in it. 2) You can put fruit (both soft and hard).  But I\'d cut it up first, obviously. 3) Fantastic for shakes.  I use it for my shakeology - perfect!!! 4) RECOMMENDATION - The power button is not meant to be pressed and held for longer than 5-8 seconds.  If you have a lot of ice cubes or an apple in there, then try \"pulsing\" the power button, that is, press it intermittently until you get your desired smoothie texture. 5) Very small footprint - you can put it in your desk drawer or luggage if you\'re traveling 6) RECOMMENDATION - Get extra lids and tumblers.'),
(3147, 6, 1, 1, '2016-08-17', 'Toasting one side only!! Just returned second toaster which only browned on one side!  Called Cuisinart with the problem and they said to just return it! Not sure how it received such good ratings by so many when 2 I ordered both had same issue!.'),
(3148, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-28', 'One Star It lasted 1 day'),
(3149, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-28', 'Disappointed with the controls Disappointed with the controls. Its hard to set the control for toasting - Every time I set it, it gets too dark or too light. The knob is very had to turn. With my previous toaster I could set and leave my favorite setting at the desired level. And when I want to toast the next time, I just have to push one button. With this one every time I have to find the correct setting.  Pretty bad design of the controls. And sometimes when I try to turn it off by turning the knob counter clockwise, it goes into stay ON state. Its dangerous as I could accidentally leave it on and leave the house thinking I turned it off.  It  just passed the 1 month window to return and I am stuck with this.  very disappointed.'),
(3150, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-09', 'Excellent product. The balck print on the stainless finish ... Excellent product. The balck print on the stainless finish is hard to read and the raised line on the knobs should be a lit bigger.'),
(3151, 10, 1, 1, '2015-06-04', 'Takes forever to blend. Took me 10min just to ... Takes forever to blend.Took me 10min just to blend up some fruit.'),
(3152, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-14', 'this is a great toaster oven Functionally,  this is a great toaster oven, but the cord is way too short at 2 feet.'),
(3153, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-08', 'Good little blender This blender works pretty well for small shakes and smoothies. I\'ve bought two of them and one as a gift. They\'ve worked really well and I will keep using them. The motor isn\'t extremely strong, but it works well for smaller things. If you\'re looking for a high powered blender, you\'ll probably want something else. I\'ve known a few gym fanatics that also use this one. It works well for one person. Large frozen chunks get stuck in the blades sometimes, so make sure you\'re not putting too much in it!'),
(3154, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Easy to program Easy to program. Removable water compartment is a GREAT feature! Brews really hot. For the price, this is an excellent coffee maker.'),
(3155, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'Five Stars My son loves this. Uses it every day.'),
(3156, 9, 1, 3, '2015-12-27', 'I love that there is no carafe and it keeps your ... I have had this coffee maker for a year. I would rate it 4 stars except for the cord issue. Most everyone, including me, thinks the cord is 3 inches long. I finally saw where one person had posted that you have to pull really hard on the cord and it extends to about 16 inches. I mean you will think you are about to break it! Cuisinart should really give some explicit directions for this. I pulled on it when I bought it a year ago thinking there was no possible way the cord could be so short and came to the conclusion it was fixed. It was only after deciding it was time to come up with a fix or replace with a different machine I discovered it was retracted. Other than that, I have no complaints. I love that there is no carafe and it keeps your coffee at a nice drinking temperature for several hours (not if you enjoy your coffee SCALDING hot, though). I love the programmable feature. I did drop the reservoir and chipped it, but have ordered a new one.'),
(3157, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Perfect upgrade I have had a Keurig mini for years and decided I needed an upgrade. The K200 is perfect for me. It\'s not very bulky and fits in the same spot as my mini did. I like that it has several options for cup sizes and I can make a Carafe as well. Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review'),
(3158, 4, 1, 4, '2015-06-30', 'Great toaster oven, but no timer for baking Not bad for a toaster oven. Toasts very nicely and the oven seems very consistent; the best I\'ve used over the past 30-odd years. Would rate 5 stars except for three things: no timer, so don\'t doze off while you\'re baking that fish filet. Two: the eardrum-piercing, heart-stopping beeps at the end of the toast cycle. Three: the hard to read markings on the dials. Even so, this is a very nice unit and I hope it lasts longer than my previous toaster ovens (avg life expectancy, 2 years). I\'ve had it for about a year. It\'s the only toaster oven I\'ve ever owned that can actually toast English muffins or bagels beautifully without drying out the bread, or burning it to a cinder. Baked potatoes are perfectly done. Lasagna, no problem. Excellent performance at a reasonable price, IMO.'),
(3159, 11, 1, 3, '2014-06-21', 'too small, bakes and broils at the same time I gave it to a friend.for a few $ more u can do better.  I bought the  Miallegro 5380 and I extremely happy'),
(3160, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-18', 'Four Stars works well'),
(3161, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-12', 'Five Stars Plenty big for the 2 of us. Bakes evenly and we use it daily.'),
(3162, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-28', 'it\'s a great personal blender it\'s a great personal blender. I love making fruit smoothies using this blender. I would make sure to have some fluid when blending frozen fruits to make it easier for the blender to work.'),
(3163, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-05', 'Five Stars Very fine toaster oven.  Swift delivery.  Thank you'),
(3164, 2, 1, 2, '2015-11-26', 'Burnt Plastic SmellReturned This toaster oven produces a very strong burnt plastic smell when used.  Other reviewers have mentioned this as well.  Some say the smell went away, as mine did initially, but it came back, and I will be returning the product.  I contacted customer support for the company, and they let me know that the smell was normal for a new item but completely dodged my question about what was causing the smell.  I do not feel comfortable using this product in my house. I added the second star because it does toast bread pretty well.'),
(3165, 7, 3, 1, '2015-05-12', 'It actually worked very well for the first 5 brews, but then it completely stopped working. I tried cleaning and fixing it based on the troubleshooting section in the manual, but nothing worked. I loved the concept of being able to use it with K-Cups or coffee grounds, and it did make a great-tasting, quick cup of coffee. I was recommending it to everyone I knew because of how wonderful it was working and because of the low price. Maybe I just got a lemon, but I have returned it and will not be getting another like it. I guess I\'ll just have to stick with Keurig, even though they cost so much more money.'),
(3166, 7, 3, 4, '2015-01-23', 'I have had this coffee maker about 2 weeks. It works the same as the Kuerig but at half the price. It does take a little longer to brew though.'),
(3167, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-06', 'good coffee The coffee maker is great, but the gold basket is hard to clean well.. you may be better off with paper.'),
(3168, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Five Stars Love this. Good for warming leftovers, dinner rolls, making toast. I also use the top for warming plates .'),
(3169, 10, 1, 4, '2016-07-31', 'Four Stars Love it.'),
(3170, 3, 1, 5, '2014-08-06', 'works great for me I love this guy.  Takes a little getting used to the controls but it works great.  It is big enough to take the place of an oven for many tasks and will stop on a timer. I do use the oven setting for pizza rather than the pizza setting, because the thin pizzas I get at trader joes take less time than the average supermarket one I guess, but that is no hassle really.'),
(3171, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-07', 'It is easy to use This product far outdistanced my expectations.  It is easy to use, the oven bakes beautifully and it is a snap to clean following the directions in the booklet.  I can do almost everything I could do in my larger oven--but with more reliability. And it\'s so quiet!  I love my Cuisinart TOB-40 Custom Classic Toaster Oven.'),
(3172, 5, 1, 2, '2016-04-17', '... for my office on my desk as a simple easy solution. It makes very \"meh\" coffee I got this for my office on my desk as a simple easy solution. It makes very \"meh\" coffee, esp when compared to my Cuisinart I use at home. The noise level is normal, not quiet, but not loud when brewing. The face plate broke off after about 15 uses, the unit is still usable, but now it looks very ugly.'),
(3173, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-28', 'Five Stars It met my expectations'),
(3174, 10, 1, 4, '2015-09-15', 'It works great for that I use this to mix my protein shakes. It works great for that.'),
(3175, 11, 1, 4, '2014-02-28', 'This toaster is excellent for the size and price Once removing the upper crumb tray (there\'s already a catch-all tray shaped like a cookie sheet at the very bottom), the result is an even golden brown (heavy wheat bread) toast in under 3 minutes. At $35 and with quite modest counterspace usage, I see no reason to ever own a regular toaster again.'),
(3176, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-12', 'not very good at making toast I had to go out and ... not very good at making toast I had to go out and buy a toaster and don\'t like the knobs on the toaster oven'),
(3177, 11, 1, 3, '2014-11-22', 'You get what you pay for We needed a small toaster oven, and this is small. It\'s toasting dial takes a bit of getting used to and I\'m finding it takes longer to bake or heat things up in this, which makes me suspect it\'s not quite as hot as I\'m setting it. The outside of the toaster gets HOT when its used. That said, it was cheap. Next time, I\'m going to bite the bullet and buy and under counter mount oven, which costs lots more, presumably because it actually keeps the heat inside the toaster.'),
(3178, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-09', 'Five Stars LOVE IT.'),
(3179, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-09', 'Five Stars Good coffee great price.'),
(3180, 5, 1, 1, '2015-01-31', 'What a piece of crap. If you are considering going with Hamilton for ... I bought this. Attempted to use it one time. What a piece of crap. If you are considering going with Hamilton for a coffee maker you are an idiot just like I was. Well I returned mine so no longer am I one. Don\'t be an idiot like me. Purchase a coffee maker from someone that actually specializes in coffee products.'),
(3181, 12, 1, 4, '2015-10-24', 'I like french bread and this is just the right size ... I like french bread and this is just the right size to bake a frozen french roll... I have another one  just like it, but it\'s getting old and doesn\'t toast so well any more...wanted to replace it while I still had the chance to get the same item (it\'s not easy to find)'),
(3182, 7, 3, 3, '2015-01-06', 'very convenient'),
(3183, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-09', 'I chose this one because i liked the design of it and that it held 4 ... Our old toaster oven croaked after many many years so we were in need of a new one. I chose this one because i liked the design of it and that it held 4 slices of toast! our old one only did 2. I also liked that where the dials are it tells you what each setting is, i noticed on other there was just a symbol and that i\'d have to remember what each one was. I\'m sure with time it wouldn\'t be that big of a deal but it just seemed better to have it written on there. My only complaint is that for the toasting feature it\'s a bit hard to turn the knob back to the toasting setting after turning it past the \"10\" marker. I don\'t know if it\'ll get easier with time because it\'s brand new but other than that everything else has worked out fine. My kids are finally glad to have their waffles and toast in the morning. I hope my review helped you with your decision whether or not to buy this product. When i buy products i try my best to give an honest and unbiased review whether or not i received it free, at a discount or paid full price.With that being said, I did not receive this product free or at a discounted price for my honest review. I enjoy helping others where others have helped me. Thanks for taking your time to read my review!'),
(3184, 10, 1, 4, '2015-07-26', 'Convenient! Works fantastic. Very convenient for taking on the go.'),
(3185, 10, 1, 1, '2015-04-13', 'Doesnt blend all the way Doesn\'t blend all the way.  Decent option but not high end and leaves lots of chunks no matter how long you blend it for.'),
(3186, 6, 1, 3, '2015-02-14', 'Three Stars Cheap import!'),
(3187, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Five Stars does a very good job,makes a good cup of coffee.'),
(3188, 8, 1, 5, '2014-08-19', 'Five Stars excellent product'),
(3189, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'Five Stars Good value. performs as described.'),
(3190, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-28', 'Great personal blender I ordered this product a few weeks ago and so far so great! I use it on a daily basis for my smoothies which include frozen fruit. I was nervous to use it with the frozen fruit but it blends with no problem! It\'s super easy to clean and I love the convenience of the lid. Even though it\'s good for on the go, I don\'t take it with me because it\'s too big for my comfort on the train but if you drive, it\'s a perfect fit for the cup holder. You won\'t regret this buy!'),
(3191, 6, 1, 4, '2015-12-29', 'It seems to work great at toasting bread This toaster looks clean and bright.  It seems to work great at toasting bread.'),
(3192, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-17', 'Good brewer and worth a buy I\'ve had this brewer for a couple of weeks.  I am the coffee drinker in the house, but my wife likes an occasional hot tea in the morning.  We have tried both in the brewer.  So far we are sold on this brewer.  It is slim enough to fit in the space we have in the kitchen. My wife was especially pleased that she could choose a color for the brewer.  Oh, by the way, the coffee and tea tastes just fine.  We will try to find a substitute for the K-cups as they are somewhat expensive (retired and on a limited budget).  All and all I would recommend this brewer to folks who want a quick cup of coffee or tea, without very much effort.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3193, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'we like it, nice wide slots for Works well, we like it, nice wide slots for slices'),
(3194, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-25', '5 stars for a great coffeemaker Love it.  Works fast.  Easy to use and clean.'),
(3195, 4, 1, 3, '2015-01-11', 'Weak door hinge Had ours about a year and the door hinge broke. Everything else has worked fine. Won\'t buy this model again because the door hinge is one of those parts that gets used multiple times at every use.  It should be one of highest quality parts on the oven.'),
(3196, 8, 1, 4, '2016-04-28', 'Four Stars good'),
(3197, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-23', 'Wishing for watertight; a blendering sequel for all ages This is a blender.  I really wish it was watertight.  That would be tight.  Water.  Only a few uses in but functioning well so far!'),
(3198, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-31', 'Good Product Have had this for about 2 years now still works well. toasts evenly.'),
(3199, 7, 3, 4, '2015-05-08', 'I have always wanted one of the more expensive varieties but didnu2019t want to spend the money. Now I can have the same experience at a fraction of the price. I have used the name brand one cup and was impressed. I like the flavors that are offered by K-cups and this product allows me to drink them. I will start with the good qualities of this product. It looks stylish and can fit the decor of any kitchen. Itu2019s small enough to be used in bedrooms or dorm rooms. You can use all of the varieties of K-cups or you can use regular ground coffee. Now the bad qualities of this product. Instructions say that you can use regular ground coffee with this and you can. What it doesnu2019t say is how big of a mess it is to use regular ground coffee. The first test I did for this product was the ground coffee test and although I was happy that it did its job, I was not happy when I had to bang the grounds out of the mesh filter. This product has a regular setting and a bold setting. The only difference in the two is that you will have more coffee silt on the bottom of your cup with the bold. But that isnu2019t saying much because you will have it with both settings. Also, I wouldnu2019t recommend using this with the regular coffee grounds but if you do use it for that take a moist paper towel and wipe the rubber seal on the top of the coffee maker. If you donu2019t you will have a buildup of old coffee and germs.'),
(3200, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-27', 'This is a great little oven This is a great little oven, space saver. No complaints! I use it to bake for one or two. I use it for reheating.'),
(3201, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-15', 'I love this thing I love this thing!! Only problem is I can\'t fill up my tall travel cups but I just use a regular coffee cup and then dump it into the mug. It\'s much easier to clean than I expected and it looks really nice. Beware, though, of using a lot of course coffee grounds with paper filters. Sometimes the hot water flows up to and over the edge as the water flows out slower than it flows in. If that\'s your case, then use the included gold reusable filter.'),
(3202, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-02', 'Handle with care Works very well and easy to clean. Do not put ice in there, it will break down.'),
(3203, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-29', 'I really like the Kureig Model 250 I have used a regular coffee maker for many many years. My wife and I both like caffeinated coffee.  Recently I decided to drink only decaffeinated coffee. This created a problem in the morning because my wife wanted to continue drinking caffeinated coffee.  I recently purchased a Kuerig coffeemaker and have been extremely pleased with its performance.  Now I can quickly brew as many cups of coffee as I wish without disturbing my wife\'s routine.  I\'m now trying different flavors because of the wide selection. I would recommend the Kurig system to anyone.'),
(3204, 7, 3, 4, '2014-01-20', 'This coffee maker is great in that it can take ground coffee, k-cups and pods. When you remove the cup holder for a larger cup, but not real tall, the coffee splashes a bit. A couple of times, it seems it did not disperse all the water and then when I removed the cup after it had turned off, it continued to drip. That doesn\'t happen most of the time, but it did happen a couple of times. Not sure why. Also, it does take a bit longer to brew than a keurig.'),
(3205, 4, 1, 2, '2015-08-12', 'Unsafe! The top get extremely hot to the touch ... Unsafe! The top get extremely hot to the touch and the oven would tilt trying to open the door. Was returned!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(3206, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-22', 'How to Start the Day as a Human This Hamilton Beach product is an attractive, reliable drip coffee maker, the kind that has the blessed black liquid ready for you as the day hatches.  So you can stagger into the kitchen drawn forward by the comforting smell of fresh coffee and work your phone with one hand, whisk scrambled eggs for an omelette with the other, and drink your java through a foot long, heat-resistant straw (not included) while slowly regaining consciousness.  This pleasant scenario assumes, of course, that you remembered to fill the handy removable reservoir, add coffee to the front-loading basket and program the machine the night before.  Hamilton Beach is a tried and true brand, and the price is reasonable for what you get, low enough to perhaps leave room in the budget for high-quality coffee.  Which, after all, is the main ingredient, that and spring water. The strength of your brew is a factor, too, which means a significant part of the final product has to do with how you prepare it. You will enjoy a number of agreeable features.  The controls are fairly intuitive, even for gadget-challenged users.  You can make a few cups or a full pot of 12.  Your second cup will still taste good thanks to the stay-warm feature, which protects the brew from that awful burnt taste.  (They do mean warm, though.  It wont be hot, but thats where a microwave comes in.)  I like the light heft of the pot, and the way it snicks into its cradle so you know it is seated properly. Yes, the pot is plastic and maybe we are all going crazy from exposure to plastic compounds, but glass is heavy and it breaks.  Another feature is the clever removable basket that holds the filters, which makes for easy transport across the kitchen.  Or you can order a permanent filter basket as an accessory.  You may not achieve that perfect cup of coffee we all dream about, but most days a decent cup of coffee waiting in the kitchen as one tries to regain human form is something to be grateful for.'),
(3207, 3, 1, 4, '2014-08-11', 'the oven works fine. I\'m no cook and it doesn\'t tell me ... the oven works fine. I\'m no cook and it doesn\'t tell me how to cook various foods. I mean step by step operation for various foods. BUT I\'M NOT COMPLAINING.'),
(3208, 6, 1, 4, '2016-05-21', '... little light compared to older toasters but does a good job with bread and English muffins Toaster seems a little light compared to older toasters but does a good job with bread and English muffins.'),
(3209, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-17', '... have had this for two months now and still love it! There is definitely a learning curve with ... We have had this for two months now and still love it! There is definitely a learning curve with how to work it compared to our previous simple toaster oven. But it works so nicely for toasting large sourdough bread pieces or a roasted veggie side for dinner. I love the convection aspect of this too.'),
(3210, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-20', 'A great buy! I love it. It was a great choice. Good for apartments'),
(3211, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-20', 'Five Stars Love it, so much betterthan my old one.'),
(3212, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-18', 'Great investment for the price This is a great machine and love all the features of this unit. Maybe in future models or larger models the carafe stays hotter, otherwise a great investment'),
(3213, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-17', 'One Star Don\'t waste your money.  No power'),
(3214, 5, 1, 3, '2014-12-11', 'Nice coffee maker, but poorly designed parts. I really like this  coffee maker, but after about 4 months the panel that covers the buttons on top broke off simply from the opening and closing of the coffee filter compartment. I love the way the water reservoir works, but with that piece broken the hot steam gets into the electronics and things are starting to melt. This is a poorly designed piece, with only two flimsy pieces of plastic holding it to the maker.'),
(3215, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-07', 'Works great! Just as you\'d expect Works great!  Just as you\'d expect.'),
(3216, 4, 1, 2, '2016-08-26', 'Worked well...until it didn\'t. We liked this toaster oven for reheating food and making cheesy toast, but almost exactly at the two year mark, something really disturbing happened. The toasted stopped shutting OFF and seemed to be heating up to full heat. i.e., it burned the toast and then would not shut off...kept going. We will be purchasing another toaster oven from a different company rather than risking this kind of safety hazard in our home.'),
(3217, 3, 1, 3, '2016-03-29', 'Three Stars died after less than two years of use in a household of two adults.'),
(3218, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-11', 'Love my keurig 2.0!!! The Keurig 2.0 is awesome. It is easy to use. Love the digital touchscreen. The option to brew a single cup or a carafe is great. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3219, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-02', 'Five Stars very happy'),
