(3228, 12, 1, 3, '2015-05-31', 'I like the looks love the toaster part I like the looks love the toaster part, a snap to clean but the toaster oven part is small big enough for a McDonald\'s Breakfast sandwich or 1 slice of bread..'),
(3229, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'Great coffee pot This coffee pot work great very easy to clean great product had it about 6 months now never had a problem'),
(3230, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-07', 'so good. Nothing is broken nor leaking Hey so far, so good.  Nothing is broken nor leaking; I\'ve only been using it for a few days but it brews a good cup of coffee. I programmed it on a timer and it works fine. The design is quite nice and it takes up little counter space (a plus in my one-wall kitchen), and I really like that I can remove the water chamber when cleaning it out daily. I plan to post a follow-up review to let everyone know if it still is okay after a few months.'),
(3231, 10, 1, 3, '2015-11-02', 'Three Stars lovely'),
(3232, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-19', 'Five Stars We love our Cuisinart TOB-40, Better than expected.'),
(3233, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-30', 'A lot of buttons for a little toast I bought this to replace an aging version, which was I was unable to get truly clean after 15 years. I thought the crumb pan in this BLACK+DECKER would make cleaning easier, but since it lacks a lip in the back and you have to tip it to get it out it just drops crumbs in back. The crumb pan also doesn\'t clean up nicely in the dishwasher, so it should be hand washed. It does toast things nicely, but you have to manipulate three different setting to get that done. Also, unlike my old over, it doesn\'t turn off the toasting feature when you open the door and you have to be careful when you turn it off that you don\'t switch it too far because that is where the stay-on feature is-- a mistake I have already made once. The picture makes it look like there is more room in the oven than there actually is so while I used to be able to put slightly overfilled ramekins in my old oven, it isn\'t possible to do so with this oven, so I was disappointed in the height dimension. You could toast four small pieces of bread,but many specialty breads you will only be able to fit two slices. It is a decent toaster oven that doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space, and for the price it is worth it.'),
(3234, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-28', 'It\'s getting toasty in here! It\'s a toaster over and it does what it\'s supposed to do. Has nice features at this price. Easy to use.'),
(3235, 5, 1, 2, '2017-01-19', 'I would have given this 5 stars if it did ... I would have given this 5 stars if it did not already come to me with a broken face plate.'),
(3236, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-18', 'Bang for Buck Perfect size for a single guy. Very nice, basic coffee pot for when you don\'t have time to use your French press.'),
(3237, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-26', 'Five Stars Love this coffee pot,  (fantastic) easy to set up & program.'),
(3238, 12, 1, 3, '2016-09-22', 'Still working, but could be improved I have been using this toaster for a while now; it\'s still working well. That being said, it\'s not perfect, especially the toaster part. Regular bread and anything thinner is better made in the oven part, as it will curl from the heat if made in the toaster. This unfortunately takes away the convenience of a toaster that toasts bread on both sides at the same time. The toaster part works okay for thicker breads like bagels and English muffins. The toaster oven works fine, like a broiler, so you will have to turn over whatever you are cooking if you want to toast both sides. I highly recommend a short roll of tin foil to use on the cookie sheet included as it is not a non-stick surface. It\'s also not the easiest thing to clean; even though there is a removable crumb tray, many crumbs still fall beneath it and it\'s hard to remove them all. That being said, my someone in my family does use this at least once a day, so it was worth getting.'),
(3239, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Keurig 2.0 series Love this machine. I have always had Keurig machine. Works well. If any problems they are great to deal with. They will always help you out. I like the extra large water tank so you don\'t have to keep filling it and I like the size of the cups you can use. Very user friendly.'),
(3240, 5, 1, 2, '2016-03-25', 'Front cover lose and no mid-brew cups. The front cover keeps popping off.  Sometimes if you want to get a cup before it is done brewing, coffee will continue to brew and spill out onto hot plate.  It\'s functional for the most part.'),
(3241, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Five Stars Love! My favorite Coffee Maker so Far! Love the option to add the Carafe!'),
(3242, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'It brews my coffee in the perfect strength that I want It brews my coffee in the perfect strength that I want. I love that I have multiple choices on what size cup I want. It\'s so easy and convenient for when I am busy. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(3243, 7, 3, 4, '2015-08-19', 'I love the flexibility of this coffee maker, brews great mug faster than Keurig and you can use ground coffee BUT I find that the standard coffee pods do not fit only the smaller pods with mesh containers work, that\'s ok I can buy that kind but it seems odd even the samples they included are too big for this machine ??'),
(3244, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-26', 'This is one of the best coffee pots I\'ve ever owned This is one of the best coffee pots I\'ve ever owned. Brews coffee fast, hot, and delicious. Setting it up takes a bit getting used to because of the different reservoirs you need to take care of, but that\'s quickly overcome.'),
(3245, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-28', 'Hamilton Beach blender I LOVE this blender.  This is the second one I\'ve purchased, I wore out the first one!  Use it for smoothies and milkshakes.'),
(3246, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-16', 'Big help for us I was able to reheat leftover foods last night using this thing and it was a big help for us.'),
(3247, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-07', 'WORTHLESS VERY DISSAPOINTED, USED ABOUT 6 TIMES AND THE GASKET / SEAL FOR CONTAINER BROKE SO IT LEAKED BAD, THREW IN THE TRASH !'),
(3248, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-01', 'Awesome!!!! I love it!! And it\'s portable! I recommend for everyone! It saves me in the morning and it\'s cheap!'),
(3249, 6, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Four Stars Simplicity of toaster; wideness of toast area; ability to defrost'),
(3250, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-12', 'Five Stars It\'s a toster. what can I say?'),
(3251, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-03', 'Good size for RV. We use this for our RV and it is the perfect size.'),
(3252, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-29', 'I don\'t like that every 3rd pod I use out of a ... I don\'t like that every 3rd pod I use out of a box of coffee does not work in this machine. I have yet to look up and see if I can get around this. I have a travel on so make my coffee in it when pod doesn\'t work. Would like a 12 oz cup of coffee and not a 10. I think Keurig is doing their customers a big disservice by not allowing all k cups in their coffee maker. Thought this would be good so I could make bigger cups for company. So far have not used that service. Wish coffee was hotter. This is my 3rd Keurig coffee makers and most dissatisfied with this one.'),
(3253, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-25', 'Fast and efficient for my morning cup o\' joe I love this coffee pot, it makes just the right amount. No waste. It makes a nice pot in under 3 mins. I am very happy with it.'),
(3254, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-27', 'Five Stars perfect.'),
(3255, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-15', 'My husband and I really like the convenience of the FlexBrew. We each get whatever type of coffee we want, it is ready quickly right into our cups or to-go mugs. We like the ease of just pouring the amount of water we choose, and whether we want ground coffee or K Cups. Even just hot water for tea. Cleaning is easy and hassle free, also. The only negative thing is that it is noisy but after a while you just don\'t notice it. We have recommended this Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffeemakers to several of our friends.'),
(3256, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-10', 'Hurrah...not one beep out of it! Hurrah!  Found a coffee maker that does not beep even once!!!!  So thrilled.  I\'ve got 2 Kitchen Aid coffee makers, one I use and one as a spare, the Kitchen Aid beeps so many times during its use and the brew button flashes BRIGHTLY when you have it set for coffee the next day. It is annoying as hell.  I need a coffee maker for our new RV I looked and looked and asked questions and finally after confusing answers to my question I purchased this one.  I just opened the box and set it for a water run on the timer...said to myself...wait for it, wait for it and it never happened!  So if you don\'t want your coffee maker to beep you clear across the house, wake the dog up and have your kitchen flashing all night this coffee maker is your answer! It is very easy to use, the design of the controls are great didn\'t even read the book to have to figure it out!  Love the features this Hamilton Beach has; easy fill removable water container, unit swivels to easily get to the water container...just everything about it is great!  (Can\'t say the same for the Kitchen Aid, never can get the cleaning button off!)  So I\'ve once again learned buying expensive does not give you the best!.'),
(3257, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Favorite blender! Can take to work Favorite blender! Can take to work, easy to carry on trips and I even used it in my car.'),
(3258, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-19', 'Five Stars Great product and price.'),
(3259, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'Five Stars great product'),
(3260, 8, 1, 5, '2014-07-02', 'Small and Simple Serving us Well Brews 5 cups in about 2-3 minutes!  We\'ve been using it for a couple years now and continues to work properly with it\'s simple design.  We use paper filters in it for ease of cleaning.'),
(3261, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-03', 'Still love it! I\'ve been using this for around 3 months and I still love it.  Filling the water container is very convenient.  It doesn\'t drip when you pour.  The filter is easy to access.  I would buy it again and would recommend it to my friends.'),
(3262, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-05', 'Five Stars Very happy with this product.'),
(3263, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-22', 'Beautiful Oven. This toaster oven is a Beaut to Behold. It does it\'s job and the silver and black color is great. But 4 slice toaster???, I don\'t know,your bread slices wouldn\'t have any room,plus the only pizza that can fit in this oven would be one of those single serve pizza\'s,(NOT A NINE INCH PIZZA). I kept the oven,though small and gave it 4 stars because it is a good oven and my family doesn\'t bake pizza in our toaster oven,so that \"Myth\" didn\'t apply to us anyway. It appears bigger in the picture folks,(Beware Of Size) but if size isn\'t the issue,this oven is so worth the money.'),
(3264, 12, 1, 5, '2015-12-23', 'Love it. Perfect for my needs Love it.  Perfect for my needs.'),
(3265, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-01', 'It brews a nice even consistant of joe weather I brew 2 cups ... I bought one for myself and later I bought one for my sister. It brews a nice even consistant of joe weather I brew 2 cups or 10 cups. Keeps the coffee hot without a burn taste I got from my old machine. Note: This uses the flat filters not the cone.'),
(3266, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-14', 'Five Stars I\'ve been lookin\' for a toaster like this for a long time.  PERFECT.'),
(3267, 12, 1, 1, '2014-04-28', 'Um, no It only toasts one piece of toast at a time, and it burns it. The oven won\'t accommodate a large piece of pizza, and guess what? It burns it. It\'s stylish and cute, a perfect kitchen prop. Please don\'t buy it if you actually want to toast or bake things.'),
(3268, 5, 1, 1, '2016-05-13', 'The reason why I got this was because ... I got this machine less than one month and half, abd it happened days ago. I use it once everyday, it works fine. The reason why I got this was because the design was cool. However,the fron covering panel was come off. It looks like because of vapor heat. I will keep using it because it still makes coffee,but I am totally disappointed and since there is no Hamilton Beach branche near here,I have to use that ugly product. I can see the same problem on pictures here, it\'s their big problem!'),
(3269, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'This is one of the best brewers i have had This is one of the best brewers i have had. I love it. It is fast, easy and no mess to clean. Once you try you will not be able to live without it. Thanks Keurig for this amazing product. Thank you also for the free pods for this review.'),
(3270, 5, 1, 1, '2015-08-03', 'Stopped working entirely This coffee pot stopped working after less than one year.'),
(3271, 6, 1, 1, '2015-05-08', 'Magical One-Sided Bread Burning Machine It was great - at first. Within a few weeks, it started burning one side of the bread to a carbon crisp, while only kind of warming the other. Changing the settings didn\'t help at all - bagel, defrost, warm - all of them should have been \"Turn your morning bread into a carbohydrate version of Two-Face.\" It became the appliance version of Fox News, dividing my waffles into a sort of American media landscape of polar opposites, one side against the other, wholly unbalanced and not something I ever want to wake up to. In short - bad toaster.'),
(3272, 6, 1, 3, '2015-04-21', 'Toaster works Works, doesn\'t toast the same on both sides of bread.  Bagel setting only extends toasting time, does not turn off one side of the heating elements like my last toaster did.  Price was right.'),
(3273, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'I love my new Keurig It is just the right size ... I love my new Keurig It is just the right size to fit on my counter w/ the k-cup storage underneath it It coffee comes out hot and love the fact that I can adjust the drink size and if I want it stronger. The older model didn\'t have this option. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3274, 1, 1, 2, '2016-09-03', 'Delicious, easy to use, short life First 8 months, smooth sailing. Love the convenience and ease of use. Even got 2.0 compatible reusable filters. Bought the overpriced descaling product which after first application made a difference. Now it has stopped working. Makes odd sounds and takes forever to dispense 6 oz of water. Ruins coffee pods due to super slow brew. Wrote keurig asking for assistance with no response. So, I\'m not sure I can recommend the little jewel. Am trying to run a couple of water \"brews\" to see if it helps. Will certainly update review if it does.'),
(3275, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-21', 'Love It Best coffee maker I\'ve ever had.  I ordered a second one.  Easy to fill water in the removable container in the back and the front swings open to insert the filter.  I love how you can pour coffee while it\'s brewing without spills.'),
(3276, 6, 1, 1, '2015-03-25', 'I put this at my vacation home and didnt go ... I put this at my vacation home and didnt go there for a couple months and now I cannot return it. I must have gotten a defective model it worked a couple times but then the handle to push down the toast doesnt work, the lights dont go on and it doesnt toast. :('),
(3277, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-13', 'Shop no Further! This keeps my two pot a day habit fed. I really like the adjustable warmer control; too much heat is the enemy of brewed coffee. The carafe pours well. No plastic taste/smell like some others have noted. Easy to program timer and strength settings.'),
(3278, 8, 1, 4, '2014-06-27', 'great little coffee maker other than it dont have a auto.shut off after 2 hours...and ya have to wait till its done brewing or you will have coffee dripping when you try to fill a cup...it works great....it does its job...makes coffee....'),
(3279, 1, 1, 1, '2016-04-01', 'No Improvement With This Model As our old Keurig coffeemaker started to show its age, we purchased a K250 2.0. To say we\'re disappointed is an understatement. Though the box shows dozens of coffee pods, the K250 is very picky as to those that will work, and then, often inconsistently. For example, brewing two cups with Donut Shop pods, the first worked fine, the second gave a half a cup of coffee, full of grounds, grounds all over the inside of the pod holder, and worse, a message on the screen to clean the needles, an annoying and time consuming process. Here\'s a photo of the mess afterward. Sometimes it will work again if unplugged and plugged into the electric outlet, sometimes it won\'t. Many pods that used to work now don\'t, what do we do with those on hand? Throw them out? Be aware of this if you opt to get a K250. The box shows Donut Shop as one of the pods supposedly OK for this model, with many others. But some aren\'t. How can you tell before hand? We sure expected better than this, have put the K250 on the shelf, and will use our old machine until it dies. Keurig, you can do better for you formerly loyal customers.'),
(3280, 5, 1, 4, '2014-08-03', 'Four Stars It makes great coffee, but you still have to take out from under the cabinet to fill.'),
(3281, 3, 1, 5, '2014-02-22', 'Love It While the unit is a little bigger than I would like, it does a wonderful job for my needs: broiling. I used the broiler to prepare garlic toast and a steak. The former came out nicely and evenly browned and the latter came out with the fat and meat browned the way that a proper broiler should do it. Yes, the exterior gets hot, but no hotter than the competitor\'s device that it is replacing and that one did not get hot enough to do broiling properly. This is one purchase that I am very happy that I made.'),
(3282, 12, 1, 5, '2015-03-25', 'Great price. Not fabulous but worth the money you ... Fast delivery.  Great price.  Not fabulous but worth the money you pay.'),
(3283, 3, 1, 4, '2016-04-13', 'Nice, but watch out for hot buttons. Overall, this is a nice oven. We\'ve been using it for over a year and are pretty happy. It heats up quickly, is reasonably sized and is all around pretty convenient. The only drawback to it is the buttons are metal, so if you\'re using it for multiple things, the buttons can get pretty hot.'),
(3284, 3, 1, 2, '2016-10-28', 'Huge I just unpackaged this thing and first and for most it\'s big, almost the size of my microwave and second I the first time I turn it on I\'ve got fireballs falling in the back.'),
(3285, 6, 1, 2, '2016-12-13', 'still can\'t seem to get a perfect piece of For 30 bucks its okay . Real chintzy, still can\'t seem to get a perfect piece of toast.'),
(3286, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-20', 'Five Stars good toaster, seems to toast very evenly. not much else to report.'),
(3287, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-26', 'Good value. Great unit for traveling and still have your smoothie.'),
(3288, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-19', 'A coffeemaker that is what a coffeemaker was meant to be. I love this coffeemaker for many simple reasons.  I am an avid coffee drinker, my coffeemaker probably gets used more than my television.  I have bought and have been gifted more coffee makers than I care to imagine, and regardless of the cost, most annoy me for one reason or another. This carafe doesn\'t drip all over the counter when you\'re pouring a simple cup of coffee.  When you\'re returning the carafe to the hotplate, it slides back in easily without catching on the edge of the hotplate.  The filter holder is easy to remove.  Whether you use the removable water reservoir or just pour the water into it, it\'s a snap. That\'s all I ask of my coffeemaker.  I don\'t care about all the bells and whistles some have.  I don\'t want a coffeemaker taking up half my kitchen counter.  I don\'t want a coffeemaker that I have to refer to the owner\'s manual every other day to operate.  I just want a coffeemaker that makes me a hot cup of coffee....simply...and without annoying me....and this unit is perfect.'),
(3289, 7, 3, 1, '2016-10-12', 'I bought this because i didn\'t want to spend 100 for a Keurig... well you get what you pay for even though i spent 40 dollars lol :( I ran water through this Hamilton machine at least 6 times to try and get rid of the nasty burning plastic smell. Then i read to put VODKA in it?! Well that didn\'t work either and i wasted my dang vodka :( lol. I then tried to make a cup of coffee and it was just squirting out and splashing all over my kitchen counter. I then gave up. Returned it the next day and bought the 100 dollar Keurig machine and it\'s THE GREATEST!!!'),
(3290, 6, 1, 2, '2015-04-13', 'Uneven It\'s nice looking, and inexpensive. It absolutely does not toast evenly, however. Not by a long shot. Kind of a deal-breaker for me.'),
(3291, 6, 1, 4, '2014-09-29', 'Good toaster Good toaster, fast, small footprint on counter.'),
(3292, 4, 1, 4, '2016-06-25', 'I love the Bagel setting This was a gift. I love the Bagel setting, but wish it were slightly deeper and that the cooking/baking tray fit in a little more easily.'),
(3293, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Toasts evenly and I love the cancel button This more than met expectations. Toasts evenly and I love the cancel button. It\'s relatively small and saves space,  but handles thick offerings.'),
(3294, 12, 1, 5, '2015-10-26', 'This is a great appliance! Multi-functional and easy to use This is a great appliance!  Multi-functional and easy to use.  Plus, the color is kind of retro, so it is very cool!'),
(3295, 10, 1, 5, '2016-06-07', 'Decent blender for the price, just don\'t execpt anything mind blowing. Very good little blender for the price. Just don\'t expect anything mind blowing from it, as it will make only some basic shakes and won\'t break ice very well. Pros: - Makes smooth shakes with light materials. - Strong enough to shred soft fruits like bananas. Cons: - Not strong enough to break ice without freaking you out. - Can be a bit leaky from the bottom on rare occasions (it\'s very rare).'),
(3296, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'Well made and compact! And it toasts consistently! Compact toaster that does what it is supposed to! It feels like a solid little appliance. Wish it came in fun colors, but that\'s my problem.'),
(3297, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-24', 'Awesome! You won\'t regret this purchase! Best coffee maker! Coffee is always delicious and regardless of brand you use! Love it!!'),
(3298, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-22', 'It works. This toaster oven is perfect if you\'re cooking for one or two. I use it far beyond its intended use, and have cooked almost everything in it that I would in my regular oven, like pieces of chicken, frozen pizza, potatoes, hot dogs, and bacon. I even made a small meatloaf. I wrap tin foil around the provided tray and it\'s really easy clean up. Note: for frozen pizza I have had to cut the pizza in half and bake each half separately. It does take longer to cook, maybe 3-5 minutes longer than a regular oven. The top of the unit heats up considerably, so do NOT leave anything on top, especially while broiling. Like, sometimes I put my coffee mug on the toaster oven because I know my drink will stay hot that way. I left a baked pork chop wrapped in tin foil on top and it literally started to fry.'),
(3299, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-18', 'love it Love it so far. Looks pretty works great. Couple cons the door does just falls down when you open it and it does get very Hot on the outside. But still happy with my purchase'),
(3300, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-21', 'Very good generic toaster oven Great for heating up stuff you don\'t want to do in the microwave, like anything that\'s wrapped in foil.  Does good toast too but, like most toasters, you have to watch it or it will toast unevenly.  I particularly like the timer for baking when I\'m toasting walnuts or almonds... keeps me from burning them, which I have a tendency to do.'),
(3301, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Great coffee maker I received my Keurig a few weeks ago. I ordered it to use in my college dorm and I\'ve been testing it out until I go away to school. It works fabulously, better than all of the knock off brands I\'ve tried. The instructions provided are clear and easy to follow. I can\'t wait to use this for years to come!!! I will definitely recommend this to my friends. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3302, 3, 1, 5, '2015-11-22', 'Five Stars It\'s great.  Use it daily.'),
(3303, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-28', 'Fast !!! Makes good coffee in short time.'),
(3304, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'Great toaster Bought this as a gift. She absolutely loves it. Wanted white and it is hard to find right now. Just the right size for her condo too.'),
(3305, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'Five Stars really good product'),
(3306, 7, 3, 3, '2015-01-28', 'Not the best for k-cups. It ruined a lot and they came out with just water'),
(3307, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'but i couldn\'t wait to use it and i love it already I received this keurig for my birthday for college, but i couldn\'t wait to use it and i love it already! its the perfect size for my dorm but still brews a perfect cup of coffee. Ill be majoring in nursing so i will definitely be using this, probably every day. Great product. Thanks,keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3308, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'Easy to use and easy to blend!!! My fiancee makes a lot of smoothies and she seems to enjoy making them even more after buying this blender.'),
(3309, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-23', 'Four Stars Excellent'),
(3310, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-08', 'Five Stars Very happy with this product.'),
(3311, 11, 1, 1, '2014-04-01', 'Not a good toaster oven Despite the great reviews for this, my experience was not a good one. The toaster was terrible at the one thing it should have exceled at.....toast. The bread was either barely toasted or burnt like crazy.'),
(3312, 5, 1, 3, '2016-02-09', 'Three Stars Had the unit three days and the clock/control bezel fell off.'),
(3313, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-09', 'i love the coffee maker. the only problem is the water resavoir is to small. other than that it is great/'),
(3314, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-29', 'Four Stars So happy I purchased this.  Nice size, easy to adjust for different uses, works well and looks good!'),
(3315, 12, 1, 1, '2014-02-19', 'Toastation Toaster/Oven Was Defective Upon Arrival The toaster function on the unit does not operate, and did not from the time I opened the package.. It must be returned. Oven function does work as intended.'),
(3316, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-05', 'Five Stars only toaster oven in MY life  second one I have owned.'),
(3317, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-26', 'I looked for a regular toaster,. but got ... I looked for a regular toaster,. but got this hoping it was not too big on counter space and my wife loves it ., She uses it far more than a toaster .,'),
(3318, 2, 1, 1, '2016-08-10', 'One Star It only toasts one side of the bread...awkward.'),
(3319, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Nice Color My daughter asked for this special color. It was perfect and has served her well.'),
(3320, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-02', 'Five Stars Perfect.'),
(3321, 1, 1, 3, '2016-03-22', 'Oops! Oops! This does not work with the updated cups....half the time and requires me to unplug the unit for a reset. The coffee made is usually much weaker than my original Keurig single cup maker unit.  I am still learning (trying to discover) how to make a normal strength cup of coffee.  One of the things I have not purchased with Amazon since my wife had a 30% off at Kolhs and the unit is on sale as well.  Got it for a little on nothing with her Kolhs cash included.'),
(3322, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-21', 'No issues, great price, realistic to it\'s timer and doesn\'t burn on settings it shouldn\'t. Works like a gem. Bought it for my girlfriend because she toasts everything! For the price you can\'t beat it. Have had no issues for multiple months now and I would buy it again.'),
(3323, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-13', 'Four Stars ok'),
(3324, 3, 1, 2, '2015-10-28', 'Broke again This is my 2nd go around with this product and it broke again.  Lasted just over a year.  Seems all four bulbs break at same time and you can\'t replace them.  I do use on a daily basis, but expect a product to last longer than this.'),
(3325, 12, 1, 4, '2014-12-27', 'This is a great little appliance This is a great little appliance! Had bigger toaster ovens but this works FAST and is just big enough. One little draw back is crumbs gather in the crack when you open the door but that is the only drawback no biggie.'),
(3326, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-04', 'Toaster oven Works well, makes nice even toasted toast and open faced sandwiches.'),
(3327, 12, 1, 5, '2016-10-07', 'Saves space and money! I love being able to save space without sacrificing utility.  This is attractive in my kitchen, makes great toast and a convenient way to heat things up without having to use my big oven.  It is a win/win!  I save space and money.  The toast was perfectly toasted, better than my toaster.'),
(3328, 4, 1, 1, '2015-11-20', 'GLASS DOOR EXPLOSION My husband and I received this toaster oven as a wedding gift.  We used it for about one week and everything seemed fine.  Then one evening as I was just about to turn around and peer into the toaster oven to see if my mozzarella sticks and taquitos were done, I heard a loud pop beside me. The glass door had exploded into thousands of tiny shards of hot glass; some pieces were blown four feet from the oven; most landed within a couple of feet from the oven. The glass was so hot that it began to stick to my counter top and was very difficult to remove.  What if one of us had been standing near it, or looking into the oven, or opening the door at the time? Burns and blindness could easily have resulted.  This is a very dangerous oven  DO NOT BUY!'),
(3329, 5, 1, 4, '2016-10-23', 'Broken \"faceplate.\" Good coffee! Well sure enough... I thought I\'d be different, but the control cover popped off for me after less than a week! I was cleaning it when this happened but I was able to snap it back into place and it holds as long as I don\'t tug it off again. I\'ll try hot glue if it starts being a problem. Other than that, the coffee is great! One thing: because the pot sits inside of a little \"nook\" it\'s actually kind of hard to glance and see how much coffee is in the pot.'),
(3330, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-29', 'Five Stars Love it. Our favorite coffee maker so far. Clean, easy to use.'),
(3331, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-27', 'Coffeemaker Makes great coffee....has a good design....love the back water container instead of having to pour the water in from the pot.'),
(3332, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-29', 'Five Stars We love it.'),
(3333, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-19', 'Five Stars A great value compared to other toaster ovens.'),
(3334, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-07', 'Five Stars Beautiful color and I love the size of the unit.  Very quiet and quick.'),
(3335, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'We\'ve had this toaster oven for 2 months now and it is the best one we\'ve had yet I have no complaints.  We\'ve had this toaster oven for 2 months now and it is the best one we\'ve had yet.  So far so good.  The product is solid, the price is amazing!.'),
(3336, 10, 1, 1, '2015-04-10', 'The blender it really small and fits nice in the kitchen The blender it really small and fits nice in the kitchen, but i can barley fit anything in it. I used it for 4 days now and just today the blender stopped working. First it was making a weird noise and then smoke started to come out of the blender. Next thing you know it doesnt work anymore. I unplugged it and it is still smoking. Gonna return this product.'),
(3337, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Simple Such a simple easy to use coffee maker.'),
(3338, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-24', 'Love the color and size I am a long time Keurig user and also know how quickly they can have issues.  Mine already started under brewing/not brewing at all.  I purchased the protection plan because, as I said, I know how things go tend to go wrong with these, but instead of going right to that, I searched on You Tube to see if anyone had a fix.  It was super easy-apparently the needle clogs on these pretty often.  I unclothed it and it\'s working fine. I love Keurigs.  Period.  I suggest a protection plan if it\'s cheap enough and You Tube for any problems you may encounter.'),
(3339, 2, 1, 2, '2016-09-24', 'Two Stars One heating element occasionally stops working after completely normal use.'),
(3340, 3, 1, 3, '2016-08-17', 'Cooks okay but control panel gets hot and is not at all intuitive or easy I read all the reviews and compared to how it was rated by others, it comes up short. It seems to cook food well and predictably and we have used it for roasting almonds, preparing frozen foods, and broiling fish. But it has flaws, one major and one minor. The minor flaw is that the control panel gets VERY hot when it\'s been cooking for a while. Like hard to touch hot. The major flaw is the control panel. I realize there are a lot of settings, and I appreciate that is has convection capabilities and some of the other settings, but it is not intuitive to set and start and takes way too many button pushes. The temperature control and timer are very slow to set, and if you get interrupted in the middle of it or forget to press start, you have to start over in about 5 seconds.'),
(3341, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-03', 'Five Stars it work very well love it'),
(3342, 11, 1, 5, '2014-12-16', 'Five Stars good buy.'),
(3343, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-23', 'Five Stars Gets the job done'),
(3344, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-12', 'but so far everything works great and we love it This toaster was everything I hoped it would be...we\'ve only had it a few weeks, but so far everything works great and we love it.'),
(3345, 2, 1, 4, '2015-04-02', 'Four Stars Directions are kind of complicated but I think I\'ve got it figured out.'),
(3346, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-06', 'Great for small cooking I love this thing. It heats up really well, it cooks fantastic. It\'s really a must have for anyone who cooks for 2 or fewer people at any time. It\'s great for snacks, reheating, and for when you\'re not cooking enough to warrant heating up the oven.'),
(3347, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-24', 'Value for money Works pretty well for most purposes. If u need to use it for prolonged time, i would suggest that you do not keep its button pressed, but let it stop every sometime. This will help it last longer. Very good in the price it is in. Make most of my breakfast juices using it. :D'),
(3348, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-20', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(3349, 8, 1, 1, '2015-03-22', 'One Star Broken when received'),
(3350, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-23', 'Nice kitchen addition. This is the second Black and Decker Toater Oven I have purchased. Just did a kitchen remodel and the stainless steel fits in perfectly with my other appliances. It toasts, bakes, and broils which is great when I don\'t want or need to turn on my regular oven.The older one is over 15 years old, and I have kept it to add to my craft room to use with oven bake clays. The only reasons I gave it four instead of five stars Are two things: the exterior gets very hot, and the print on the front stainless steel panel is very tiny and difficult to read.'),
(3351, 7, 3, 5, '2016-08-23', 'Intermittent leak out of the side of the unit that slides in with the coffee or K cup but only a few drops nothing major , makes a great cup of Joe'),
(3352, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', 'So far so good.. Does a fine job.  Easy to use.  Markings for toast settings (light, medium, dark) could be a little  bigger or maybe  brighter, but no burnt toast so timer works well. Top of oven does get hot.'),
(3353, 2, 1, 4, '2016-07-21', 'So much more useful than regular toaster or microwaving leftovers We have been wanting one of these for awhile. So much more useful than regular toaster or microwaving leftovers.'),
(3354, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-05', 'Nice Coffee Maker This coffee maker has excellent features that I like, including an illuminated clock and an adjustable keep warm setting. Push a button and the basket swing out for easy loading and the water tank has a large foldback cover which makes it easy to fill. And best of all, it brews great coffee.'),
(3355, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-19', 'Great coffee maker at a good price Great coffee maker at a good price.  A little loud while brewing but make a great cup of coffee.  Easy programming - at 5 am the coffee is made without me having to do anything but pour myself a cup.'),
(3356, 1, 1, 2, '2016-09-08', 'Two Stars Very cheap construction.'),
(3357, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-31', 'no hassle transaction great product'),
(3358, 5, 1, 1, '2015-08-02', 'Avoid. After a week making coffee three times a ... Avoid. After a week making coffee three times a day we decided to return it. It makes coffee that it\'s simply undrinkable. We are back to our 5 year old, $12 coffee maker for now.'),
(3359, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Five Stars I love this it works great'),
(3360, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-27', 'I loved it but it finally had served its time My previous maker was a $250 Krups unit I\'d had for 20+ years. I loved it but it finally had served its time. Researched quite a bit before buying this one and glad I did. Like the basket and water access and, there\'s even a little lazy susan swivel thing on the bottom to turn it to access the water.  Great little maker for the price.'),
(3361, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-10', 'Keep it clean! I really like this coffee maker. This is my second one. This time I will try to KEEP it cleaned, because you will see if you read reviews it can leak, and make a BIG mess to clean up.This has happened to me several times, but I\'m assuming it was actually my fault. Time will tell.'),
(3362, 5, 1, 1, '2015-06-09', 'Dead in 5 Months It\'s hard to write a review about something that was going so well only to have it all completely negated. All I can say is - when it worked I really liked this CM. But it doesn\'t matter when you can\'t even get 5 months out of it. Today I went to turn it on and it won\'t even power up. This is my second Hamilton Beach coffee maker (The other was under the \"Melitta\" name) to have issues.'),
(3363, 3, 1, 4, '2016-02-22', 'Four Stars Looks good but have only used for minor cooking.  no issues so far'),
(3364, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-08', 'Five Stars The toaster works great. I read some reviews and was glad I bought it.'),
(3365, 2, 1, 3, '2015-04-01', 'Three Stars It\'s what we paid for. No more. VERY basic.'),
(3366, 4, 1, 3, '2016-06-15', 'Painfully loud timer alarm, no broiler rack, good it\'s not a ticking timer though The timer on this toaster oven makes a painfully loud sound and it hurts my ears. It beeps 5 times and then it\'s done, just like my old one, but it hurts so bad I have to return it. I\'ve had a Cuisinart toaster oven for 15 years, and it recently developed a problem so I thought I\'d replace it with this model that looks a lot like my old one. The baking pan does not come with a broiler rack for fish and other meats. I do like that the toast option is not a ticking timer like many of the newer models of toaster ovens, but I\'m still returning it.'),
(3367, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-01', 'Five Stars works great. Fits wide slices of bread.'),
(3368, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-06', 'Nice Toaster Oven For 2 People With Limited Counter Space We\'ve been using this Toaster Oven for about a month now on a daily basis and it works great for us. It toasts evenly without having to turn toast over half way through. After two or three batches of toast we know exactly where to set the dial for perfect toast. We use it mostly for toast but I have used the baking and broiling features too and was completely happy with the results. One feature I like about this toaster oven is that you can turn it off when using the toast setting if you take your toast out before the cycle is complete.  We couldn\'t do that with my old one.  You just had to let it run through the toasting cycle before it  would shut off. This is a nice compact little oven that\'s great for two people with limited counter space.'),
(3369, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-10', 'Five Stars I bought this for a friend. She absolutely loves it.'),
(3370, 5, 1, 4, '2015-01-13', 'Four Stars great coffee maker. i\'ve had no problems in 3 months.'),
(3371, 2, 1, 1, '2016-09-23', 'Safety Issue? You get what you pay for.  This toaster gets terribly HOT on top.  Since I didn\'t feel it was  safe I returned it. Spending a little bit more it was replaced by a Cuisinart TOB 40N which we love.'),
(3372, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-15', 'While the mini worked great for just me I recently purchased a K250, an upgrade from the mini that I had since 2013.  While the mini worked great for just me, I wanted the larger machine for when I had guests.  The device that I purchased apparently had a defect in the system, as it did not heat the water much past warm.  I called Keurig customer service was as totally blown away by the response.  The agent apologized for my inconvenience, and sent me out a replacement, which I received in 2 or 3 days.  The replacement heated properly, and for the most part suited my needs.  My big wish would be that it allow me more options for amount of hot water to dispense at one time, as I often just use the hot water to brew a tea bag in my mug.  I have to \"brew\" twice to satisfy my needs.  After about 5 weeks of use, I went to use my replacement, and the screen was frozen.  I unplugged the device from the outlet twice and waited several seconds each time before replugging.  The screen was still frozen, and the other device plugged into the outlet worked, so I knew the outlet was fine, but I even moved it to another outlet, and still it was frozen, so I called customer service again.  Again, I received GREAT customer service, and again a new device was shipped.  My call was on Tuesday morning, and my second replacement arrived Thursday before 9AM.  I\'d give the Customer Service team 5 stars, but can\'t say the same for the equipment. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3373, 6, 1, 1, '2016-09-03', 'Had it less than a year with only occasional use ... Had it less than a year with only occasional use and it broke. The up/down handle won\'t stay down.  Won\'t toast even if I hold it down.'),
(3374, 1, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'Best Brewer Yet This is the best Keurig I\'ve owned. My first was wonderful but this new model totally surpasses that one. I wanted a brewer that could brew whole carafe\'s at a time and this one has that option. The coffee tastes so clean and can be adjusted to my preference. It\'s awesome that it knows what I\'m brewing and was great that it included samples of both coffee and tea. Also a big plus- customer service is the best. The sleek design fits in tighter places and I got to choose from several colors. I love how it has a separate reservoir where the water is always hot and ready and makes the wait time for morning coffee much shorter. (Also, I can use the instant hot water for other purposes if I want.) I have absolutely nothing bad to say about this new brewer. I love it! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3375, 1, 1, 1, '2016-10-08', 'Useless I\'ve owned this less than two months.  It will not brew a full 8 oz. as programmed, and then it drips another ounce after the brew cycle is complete.  Now it is leaking from the bottom.  And of course, Keurig has no one in their call centers to assist. Good thing I haven\'t invested in too many boxes of K cups, because this thing is useless.'),
(3376, 1, 1, 1, '2016-02-27', 'Very disappointed. Item arrived in a busted up box that had been taped (poorly) back together. When I opened it I found that the water tank in the back was broken into pieces. Looking further, all of the extras that were supposed to come with it (descaling solution, little sample k-cups, etc.) were all missing. Very disappointed.'),
(3377, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-22', 'Five Stars It is good product to buy!'),
(3378, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-13', 'Five Stars The BEST BEST toaster over ever!!!!'),
(3379, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-28', '... if the bread is fresh or frozen there\'s a good option to make a good toast I need a toast every morning and this does what I need it to do - doesn\'t matter if the bread is fresh or frozen there\'s a good option to make a good toast. No complaints.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(3380, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-04', 'Five Stars Our morning English muffin was beautifully toasted. Everything about this toaster oven has far exceeded our expectation.'),
(3381, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'good good to have at this price and works well'),
(3382, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-18', 'Burnt up. Opened the blender, washed it, plugged it in and was ready to make a shake. The blender refused to crush a small amount of ice and burnt up after a couple \"pulse\" presses of the button.'),
(3383, 7, 3, 5, '2015-03-01', 'This is a awesome coffeemaker for the price. I switched back to Hamilton Beach after several expensive makers broke.'),
(3384, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Quality, nice looking, good job toasting/baking If you want a small, good,  basic toaster oven get this one.  I checked out all the reviews before buying this one, and all the complaints.  Yes, some of the controls are a little odd, but they are easy to figure out, and then it is a snap.  I makes toasts fine.  Yes, it ticks while it is on, but that keeps you from accidentally leaving it on (which I did with my old oven.)  The unit looks & feels well made.& it is easy to clean the tray--it slides out from the front. This is a good value for this unit. I regularly make toast, and have warmed pizza, and baked potatoes.  All functions work well.  Easy to switch between toast & bake, but I do wish the manufacturers would make the writing a little bigger on everything.  (Yes I\'m over 50.)'),
(3385, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-27', 'Five Stars Excellent product.'),
(3386, 11, 1, 4, '2014-01-20', 'Great, Affordable Toaster This is a perfect, affordable, and compact toaster oven. My new apartment has very little counter space and this thing doesn\'t take up much room. I love the ease of use, but I did notice it doesn\'t take much time at all for this to burn things, so be sure to put the timer on for less than you actually would...especially with bagels, toast, etc. Comes with all the racks, pans, etc. that you need. Great value!'),
(3387, 2, 1, 4, '2015-06-11', 'Good toaster for the money, not great for cooking This is a great little oven for the money, but I am a heavy toaster oven user and kind of wishing I had gotten the more expensive model with a larger oven and two heating elements. It has been hard to get used to the dial for the toast (instead of a push button) and we end up with a lot of burned bread. The smaller profile means that, while my old toaster oven dish fits in this oven from a horizontal perspective, it is usually too close to the top of the oven and things just get burned. Also, the single heating element runs right down the middle and is completely exposed, so it gets dripped on a lot and will probably shorten its life. When this one wears out I will fork out for the better model. If you really just use it for toast (and not for cooking) you will probably be OK.'),
(3388, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-01', 'Melting Heating Elements I purchased this Cuisinart TOB-40 in May 2013 and initially I was really pleased with it.  I have a very small kitchen and this unit didn\'t take up half my counter space, I liked the way it looked, the ease of operation, the way it toasted the bread, baked, warmed, etc.  In fact, I like everything about it UNTIL about three months ago.  I just happened to notice that one of the heating elements on the bottom was melting and was nearly touching the bottom of the toaster-oven.  It could have happened earlier but I just noticed it then.  I have been afraid to use it as I believe it to be a fire hazard.  Since my toaster-oven is/was still under warranty, I contacted Cuisinart and I was told that I would have to pay to have it shipped back to them and that I needed to insure the package, PLUS I would have to pay Cuisinart \"a shipping and processing fee of $10.00 to have the new one shipped to me\".  I then went to Amazon.com to read the product reviews and was appalled to read that so many other people were/are having the exact same problem and were told they too were responsible for the shipping cost to return the product to Cuisinart.  I didn\'t see where anyone was told that they would have to pay the $10.00 fee for processing the new toaster.  I guess that may be a new requirement.  I think this is ridiculous since obviously Cuisinart is fully aware of this flaw in that model oven.  One can purchase a new toaster oven for nearly the same amount and not have all the hassle of packing up and returning the defective one.  Has anyone has the problem with a heating element melting with any of Cuisinart\'s other model toaster-ovens?'),
(3389, 6, 1, 4, '2015-06-10', 'Smart and good looking Smart and good looking. Good size and toasts well in 3 of 4 sides. Center heating element may be weak.'),
(3390, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-01', 'Great. My mother came over to my house Great. My mother came over to my house, saw it and i ordered two for her. One for work, one for home. Just make sure you follow the instructions to optimally use it well.'),
(3391, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Five Stars Nice little oven.'),
(3392, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-05', 'She really seems to like it. Goes really well with all her other ... Gave this to my mom for Christmas. She really seems to like it. Goes really well with all her other red appliances in the kitchen.'),
(3393, 5, 1, 4, '2016-03-14', 'First off let me say this is a fantastic coffee maker in so many ways First off let me say this is a fantastic coffee maker in so many ways. The removable reservoir, swing out basket, swivel feet and programmable brew options add up to a real winner. **Now the only negative I can find and it is a biggie... try ordering a replacement carafe for it from Hamilton Beach and it is a fairly reasonable $14 for it. Now add estimated S/H charges. My total came to $30 for the cheapest option. So a new carafe costs $30 but the complete coffee maker is currently $40 with Prime delivery. The shipping fee is from Hamilton Beach is absolutely obscene! With a stainless carafe this would be the ultimate cheap coffee maker.'),
(3394, 4, 1, 5, '2015-09-11', 'Five Stars Good service excellent toaster baker broiler oven'),
(3395, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-10', 'Great coffee maker! Awesome coffee maker. This is our 2nd one. We had our first one for over 4 years and really just wanted a new one. We drink multiple cups daily and really give it a workout. Only downside to the new one is that is has an extremely short cord... Less than 5 inches long. We will have to purchase an extension cord.'),
(3396, 10, 1, 3, '2015-09-18', 'Three Stars Doesnt blend fruit as well as I\'d like. Already looking for a bigger, better one.'),
(3397, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-06', 'Five Stars Thx!'),
(3398, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-24', 'Purchased as a gift for my brother, Purchased as a gift for my brother, who uses it every day and has not had any issues with this system'),
(3399, 11, 1, 4, '2016-01-21', 'Four Stars NICE OVEN AND NICE PRICE.'),
(3400, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-25', 'Five Stars great'),
(3401, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-19', 'Five Stars Best coffee machine ive ever had.'),
(3402, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-05', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker'),
(3403, 4, 1, 1, '2016-01-27', 'I liked this product in the beginning I liked this product in the beginning. Careful if food falls to the bottom tray--it smokes & sets off the fire alarm. Like other complaints, the front heating element is now very bent to the point I can\'t pull the bottom tray out to clean it.'),
(3404, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-04', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker'),
(3405, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-21', 'Best coffee maker I ever had Best coffee  maker I ever had. No drip pouring.'),
(3406, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-10', 'Love it Been using it everyday, warms up fast and does the job well!'),
(3407, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-30', 'I love everything about this except 2 things I love everything about this except 2 things. One being the automatic turn off in 2 hours, I know this is for safety reason, but would be better if we can program it. I usually keep my coffee maker on during the day. second being the time, if you unplug it you have to reset the time/clock which is kind of a pain.'),
(3408, 10, 1, 1, '2016-03-14', 'Tips over very easily, losing all its contents Very cheaply constructed. Supposed to function both to blend and also as a cup to drink from. The lid only sits on top. This ensures that at some point, even with extremely slight jostling, it will easily tip over and spill. This has happened to me more than once. The base is very small and is not at all stable.'),
(3409, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-30', 'Very good small coffee maker. Hey, it\'s a small but very serviceable coffee maker that does a really good job. This is my second one and the first lasted years with everyday use and I got more than my moneys worth. This one is about 3 months old now and has picked up right where the old one left off.'),
(3410, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-10', 'heat timer is for 2 hours & I did like the hamilton-beach timer was for 4 seems to be well built; very convenient; heat timer is for 2 hours & I did like the hamilton-beach timer was for 4; but do like this coffee maker'),
(3411, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', 'Great Toaster For The Money I needed a toaster that was not going to cost a bundle and would get the job done. This is it! The toasting knob is hard to turn at first, but gets smoother with each use. I find it to run on the hot/darker side. But I am figuring it all out. My family loves a toaster oven and this one does the trick. Easy to use. Inexpensive. Money well spent. We use it every day.'),
(3412, 10, 1, 5, '2016-07-04', 'Five Stars perfect.'),
(3413, 7, 3, 4, '2014-12-31', 'Works good. Not big and bulky like fancier units. I can store it away to save counter space. No water tank storage, no filters to replace, just put amount of water I need in and let it go, nice and simple, just what I was looking for. It does have from time to time a little splatter or splash when cup is filling, no big deal. If you want a smaller, less expensive, easy to use device, then this is it.'),
(3414, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-12', 'Five Stars Toaster works great, good deal.'),
(3415, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-05', 'Good toaster Works exactly as it should.'),
(3416, 6, 1, 3, '2015-11-14', 'Three Stars This toaster does not always toast evenly.'),
(3417, 12, 1, 2, '2014-08-13', 'Two Stars The Mini Oven is not high enough to heat regular rolls.'),
(3418, 4, 1, 4, '2016-07-27', 'Very nicely made, large and powerful Very nicely made, large and powerful. The only drawback is that the handle that pulls out the rack does not pull it out very far. I would recommend this.'),
(3419, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'Quality product which met my expectations! Looks good! Works well! Heats up instantly and toasts evenly!'),
(3420, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-03', 'Five Stars as pictured. fast service.'),
(3421, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Great little oven and it is really nice for two ... Great little oven and it is really nice for two people. Does a nice job warming pizza and making toast.'),
(3422, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-07', 'EXCELLENT toaster oven EXCELLENT toaster oven, I\'ve used it every day for almost a year now and it\'s the most essential tool in my small apartment kitchen'),
(3423, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'Five Stars exterior gets super hot'),
(3424, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-10', 'Great Coffee maker! I really like this coffee maker. We use this coffee maker under a cabinet so having the removable water reservoir is nice. We use to have a Mr. Coffee that was a pain to fill and only lasted 2 years. I also like the swing out filter. I would highly recommend this inexpensive coffee maker.'),
(3425, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-02', 'Took advantage of the special on coffee especially the sample packages so I can figure out which ones I like the most Enjoying my gift of this Keurig coffee maker. Took advantage of the special on coffee especially the sample packages so I can figure out which ones I like the most. Love the color! My husband loves the feature of having hot water for his tea so easy too.'),
(3426, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-02', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker only drawback is I can\'t find the charcoal filters.'),
(3427, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-18', 'Fast preheat. My wife likes it (and that\'s all that matters). We had another Black and Decker toaster oven which finally kicked the bucket after about 15 years. I bought this one because of the reviews and because the old one was so dependable. This one is great. It heats up fast and cooks evenly (thanks to the convection feature (which just means it has a fan)). This one is way more complicated than the old one, which just had three knobs, but it\'s great for reheating pizza or cooking those little frozen corn dogs. Come Thanksgiving I\'m sure we\'ll be using it to cook some side dishes, but in the meantime, I\'ll have crispy leftover pizza.'),
(3428, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-07', 'Makes Amazing Coffee Makes GREAT tasting coffee, fast & easy to use.  Controls are intuitive so out of the box use is easy.  BTW we done need to utilize the BOLD taste feature as the Regular makes smooth tasting java..'),
(3429, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Love this toaster Love this toaster! Not too big and love the dual toast on top or toaster oven below.  This is a winner!'),
(3430, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-29', 'Never buying another coffee maker.. because this one will last! I absolutely love this coffee maker, i\'ve had it for over a year now and it still is like brand new. Pros: has a bold and 1-4 cup option when making coffee all parts come apart to clean has a time start option to make coffee before you even get up the basket comes out to empty and clean cons: for some reason the face plate around the time pops off once in a while, nothing that damages the actual coffee maker, just occasionally pops off and can be popped back in can be awful loud making coffee sometimes is not going to win any races for how fast it makes coffee.'),
(3431, 10, 1, 4, '2015-10-15', 'I would recommend this. However I\'ve had mine for a few years now, it\'s very powerful.  I would recommend this.  However, my only issue is it\'s hard to clean the bottom of the container with the blade.  I wish there was someway to detach the blade for easier cleaning'),
(3432, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-03', 'Great product. Works well in our office for breakfast ... Great product.  Works well in our office for breakfast and lunch use.'),
(3433, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-30', 'Gets Toast Out More Easily I love the feature that allows the button that pushes the toast down can also raise it up to aid in getting the toast out.  We use smaller bread sometimes so that\'s a huge plus.  This is the first toaster I\'ve found that does that.'),
(3434, 7, 3, 5, '2015-02-23', 'So easy to clean. I did one K cup to see how it worked was fine. Of course as with all K Cups, the amount of water determines the strength. I usually use 8 ish ounces. Anyway, I got this to brew coffee for myself instead of brewing whole pots and I was tired of the expense of instant. So now I can make myself two or three large mugs and not waste any coffee and each is brewed when I want it. It has a normal and bold setting, I only like the bold setting for brewing coffee grounds. I normally use cheap coffee, Store brand or something, but the darker brew so the coffee comes out strong enough. I did add like a quarter lb of starbucks coffee I had ground to the regular 3 pound coffee can and it made it really nice if you like more bite in your coffee. Anyway I think once you figure out how you like to make your coffee this thing works great and very easy to clean. It took me just two trys both with the ground section filled to the line and mug size filled to line and pushed the normal button and then same setup but pushing the bold button, and I was happy with that setup and using the bold button. Well I\'m sure because of the capacity of the water tank and the normal and bold setting anyone could find their perfect setting within a couple cups. This is something I use everyday, It makes good coffee, easy to clean and will save me money, woo hoo!'),
(3435, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-14', 'Great coffeemaker Great compact coffee maker. No frills and straightforward. Makes a perfect amount of coffee for two people. Fits nicely in my tiny kitchen. Only reason I bought a new one is I broke the carafe to my old one and couldn\'t find a replacement. So I bought a whole new coffeemaker I like this one so much.'),
(3436, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-04', 'Good present for someone that loves RED! Good present for someone that loves RED!'),
(3437, 2, 1, 1, '2015-01-19', 'Cheap but not cheerful Given how well-reviewed this toaster oven was, I was very excited to get it in the mail and finally replace our old toaster oven. Unfortunately, I just caught a piece of toast on fire for the second time since we plugged this sucker in 2 weeks ago. The design is not intuitive; I either burn things or come back a few minutes later to realize that I mis-dialed the knobs and my frozen hashbrown is still completely frozen. Really regretting this purchase and, more so, throwing out our old - yet reliable - toaster oven.'),
(3438, 4, 1, 1, '2015-07-17', 'Dangerous, faulty heating elements on both ovens - stay away! I\'ve had two of these and both had the same problem with the very dangerous, faulty, defective heating elements.  This is a known problem as you can read other\'s posts from as far back as 2012.  On the first one, the bottom heating element got a large bubble in it that looked like it was going to pop any day.  It was still under warranty so Cuisinart shipped me a new one.  Got the new one last year and we have the same issue, but this time the element isn\'t getting a bubble, however  the whole element on the bottom now has an enormous bend in it and each time we use it and it\'s glaring orange, it looks like it\'s going to break.  If the bend reaches any higher it will hit the rack.  Again, this is a serious fire hazard but Cuisinart made it clear last time they would not be replacing it again for free for me, as it was past warranty.  Another reviewer from a few years ago said he reported to their Consumer Safety Board on their website and the rep came to his house and agreed it was a major hazard.  It\'s amazing that a few years later, nothing has been done to fix this.'),
(3439, 2, 1, 2, '2016-09-10', 'It looks nice enough, but next time we\'ll pay more for ... Wasn\'t aware that this toaster was so cheap that the timer ticks out loud. The knobs are hard to control also. It looks nice enough, but next time we\'ll pay more for a better product.'),
(3440, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-16', 'Five Stars I really like this coffee machine. Brews fast and no issues whatsoever'),
(3441, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-24', 'Four Stars Best toaster I\'ve ever bought.  It defrosts the bagels and then toasts them to perfection!'),
(3442, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-03', 'Love it I love this machine! I hesitated to get on the wagon due to the pods but I absolutely love it! I even have it in my favorite color orange!'),
(3443, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-16', 'Lots of bang for the buck lots of bang for the buck , reviews correct glass door problematic and cord shorter than it should be by 12. Since it looked industrial and had convection feature took a chance as a replacement for my aged B+D ( brand loyalty ). Made toast, frozen pizza , and bacon------ due to my use of heavy duty foil no problemo . Heat no problem as it sits on an antique steel stove and I use silicone oven mitt and a tea towel so glass door will not hit stove and shatter. Manual said severely truncated cord is to prevent tripping and/ or entanglement !!!!! This statement in instruction manual ( not written in pidgin English mind you ? ) could add a third reason ---- death by strangulation upon reading such an idiotic statement .Like the product and thanks to reviewers was aware of design flaws so all is good.'),
(3444, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-24', 'The inkjet printer of coffee makers First off it is huge and doesn\'t even fit under our cabinets. Second off it should be called the Apple coffee maker as it only uses its branded and of coarse heavily laden with licence fee cups. Of coarse you can just use the top cover of a Keurig branded cup and place it on top of your non branded cup. They seem to of done this on their new machine because their patent ran out in 2013 on the cups and I guess they don\'t make enough money selling a $89 simple coffee machine. Also it has no timer settings which I  find crazy for a machine at this price. With all that said I think these machines are great for banks and public places where they offer coffee love the idea just feel they should be more upfront in the descriptions about how it ONLY works with Keurig brand cups not the loose way they say just pickup Keurig branded cups.'),
(3445, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-05', 'GREAT PRODUCT! AWESOME PRICE I bought one of these when they first came out and I believe that was 13+ years ago!  YEP, you read right...I\'ve had this blender since 2003 or even earlier...I\'ve had it so long, I can\'t remember when I bought it!!  I use it daily and have absolutely NO PROBLEMS with it whatsoever.  I even throw it into the dishwasher to clean, every day!  13+ years!!  And at $14, I definitely got my money\'s worth!  I\'m buying another one for my son when he moves out on his own!  GREAT PRODUCT!  AWESOME PRICE!  FANTASTIC COMPANY (I have other Hamilton Beach products and LOVE all of them!)'),
(3446, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-19', 'Best Coffee Maker Ever! Very happy with this maker.  The water reservoir easily removes for filling and cleaning.  The filter basket opens from the front, it\'s easy to remove and clean,  controls easy to operate.  Manual easy to understand.  Has small rollers in the base  that makes it easy to move out and back so it stores under the upper cabinets on the counter but nicely moves out when ready for use, yet it doesn\'t move around when clicking the buttons on the front. We\'ve owned lots of coffee makers in our 45 years of coffee drinking, and this is the best maker we\'ve ever had, we\'ve had $200 coffee makers  and $10.00 makers, this one beats them all.'),
(3447, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-20', 'Performs much better than I expected Thanks Amazon for bringing this product to me. Performs much better than I expected.'),
(3448, 4, 1, 3, '2015-07-15', 'Problem that should no longer be happening. I initially purchased this unit in August, 2011. It smoked constantly during use for the entire time we owned it. I gave it three stars because it did work fairly well for the entire time we owned it. Until the bottom front heating element bowed upward and cracked about a week ago. The life of this unit for us as noted above was slightly less than four years. The smoking always bothered me, but we used it anyway. I noticed that other reviewers had the same problem with their units concerning the heating element cracking and causing problems with at least one person stating that it nearly burned their house down. Obviously, we are having to purchase another toaster oven. I decided to purchase the Waring 650 this time because it seemed to have an over-whelming number of positive reviews compared to negative reviews. I noticed on other models of the Cuisinart toaster ovens -- there were reviewers who indicated that they had problems with the heating element cracking as well. It seems to me that Cuisinart should have had their engineers correct this problem by now. As I stated before my unit was purchased in 2011. Four years should have been enough time to correct the problem with the heating element splitting. I will not purchase another Cuisinart product until they start doing a better job with their quality control.'),
(3449, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-27', 'Not happy as this was rated excellent Unable to return as it was after 30 days. It was set aside for awhile during a move.  After first use on regular setting the top part melted. Defect but no returns. I had to throw it away. Not happy as this was rated excellent.'),
(3450, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-11', 'Beware, the old Keurigs were user friendly and versatile but life has changed I just ordered this to replace my older Keurig whose pump is going out . . . Love the color and that\'s about it. The descriptions of the 2.0 don\'t mention that it will ONLY USE Keurig brand Kcups, or that you have to purchase KMug pods if you want a larger mug of coffee (I start the day with a 12 oz. mug and since it is an electronic device now, the machine reads the info that is preprinted on the top of the pod and tells you what size is available according to the kcup that you are using).  I have to push 6 oz. twice to get my 12 oz. until I order KMug pods and as far as I can tell, KMug pods are only available through Keurig, gr-r-r-r. Additionally, I have a bunch of older Kcups that won\'t work because they have changed the design on the tops to be read electronically - my family has moved to the east coast and Colorado and there are leftovers that haven\'t gotten used quickly; also I have a few other favorite brands (Panera, Cazo) as well that are now unusable. If all of this info was stated in the description I would have purchased one of the other brand of single coffee makers that are more user friendly. No more Keurigs here, I\'m really disappointed after loving my older Keurig, which I have had for at least five years.'),
(3451, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'this is the best toaster i have ever had this is the best toaster i have ever had, leaves nice toasted stripes on the bottom, never new toast taste so good! also use it as a oven and top broil, quick not messy really amazing'),
(3452, 2, 1, 2, '2015-06-25', 'Choices: dried out or burned - and have the OXO grippers nearby :-( This review is based on one day\'s use and, so far, I\'ve used only the toaster function.  It is going back.  The first piece of toast, set to light, came out light but totally dried out - bread crumb dry.  I set the next slice for the 1/2 darker setting and it burned to a crisp because the toaster didn\'t shut off.  It was smoking, really!  Somehow it kept moving to a setting called \"stay on.\"  The first slice at least shut off. Instructions say to turn it past 10 (very easy) and then turn back to the setting you want for the toast.  Do you know anyone at the gym with strong hands?  I had to get the rubber thingie I use to open jars to turn the dial backwards, as instructed.  What has happened to simple toaster ovens?  Thank goodness I haven\'t trashed my more than 10 year-old toaster oven (also Black and Decker).  I\'ll just go back to it.  Very disappointed in them.  I might have kept trying it for awhile longer if it didn\'t take such effort to turn the darn dial back to light and if the toaster setting would shut off every time.  Had I not been nearby, would the toast have caught fire?  I don\'t know but am not willing to take the chance.'),
(3453, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'POWERFUL. I bought this 10 YEARS AGO and I still use it all the time.  I have used a Ninja, Magic Bullet, and various other blenders, food processors, and immersion blenders.  This little guy is my favorite.  It\'s big enough for a Shakeology size smoothie even when you add a banana and lots of ice.  It\'s great for small batches too, and its POWERFUL.  It pulverizes ice. It\'s also small enough to tuck away in a cupboard.  I make a smoothie, dump it into a glass, and then rinse the blender clean right away.  (It\'s easier to clean dried-on goo from a glass than a blender. Sometimes I forget the smoothie glass in my car.  Gross.)  I have a little old hand vacuum that I love.  It\'s so old but it works GREAT.  I have actually duct taped the cracks in it, and I refuse to throw it away, because I can\'t find another vacuum that works as well, and they don\'t make this one anymore.  That\'s how I feel about this blender. I\'m buying a second one now, in case something happens to mine.'),
(3454, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-15', 'Good looking, space saving and toasts evenly Good looking, space saving and toasts evenly. I had a good toaster for several years that was really to big for my smal kitchen. When I had to replace it I wanted one that was more compact. This one fits the bill without compromising good function and i have always had good service fron this brand.'),
(3455, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-01', 'Thank you love it Works great love it the best so far.'),
(3456, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-14', 'I have stopped using it and am extremely disappointed in it This coffee maker is awful. After only two months of using it, it began to leak all over the counter. Then, the top control panel would become so hot that it couldn\'t even be touched. This coffee maker makes a huge mess and is unsafe due to how hot it becomes. I have stopped using it and am extremely disappointed in it. I will never buy a Hamilton coffee maker again.'),
(3457, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-16', 'How I Start My Day... Every morning, I wake up and have a routine I go through to start my day, this just made it easier.  My wife and I both like different types of coffee and even the ones we both like, we\'re not always in the mood for them at the same time.  It does spurt a little at the end of the cycle which may cause a little splattering, but we use large coffee cups which prevents unwanted splattering.  Bottom Line: We love our new Keurig, the only problem is trying to choose from all the great flavors available.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3458, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-06', 'Five Stars Great product. Works really well.'),
(3459, 5, 1, 3, '2016-02-19', 'The Hour Button Stopped Working In A Few Weeks The coffeemaker makes a good cup of coffee.  BUT the hour button stopped working and we cannot set the time or program it to come on in the mornings.  If you want to not have a clock that works or have coffee ready when you wake up, then this is the pot for you.  I do not know how to contact the seller to let them know about this defect.  Otherwise, no complaints.  We feel like we did not get all that we paid for.'),
(3460, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-06', 'Toaster-Oven It\'s an excellent toaster oven.Alittle difficult to get the toast the way one likes it as compared to a plain toaster.Since this does more it is more versatile.'),
(3461, 10, 1, 3, '2016-04-09', 'Terrific concept, easy to use, could use  a stronger motor. I bought it with plans to keep it at my work desk to have handy  for enjoying protein shakes as my morning breakfast. However I tried it twice this weekend and am returning it. My protein shakes consist of  a handful of frozen chopped kale, two scoops of protein powder, a teaspoon each of chia seeds, textured veggie protein, ground flax and wheat bran, plus a teaspoon of honey, a couple of berries or a small slice of avocado, all  topped off by water.  Even though I first stirred the mixture, I found that I had to stop and stir several times to get the motor going.  It did the job..eventually, with a slight rubber burn smell due to extra pulsing effort.  It would be fine for milkshakes and recipes that do not  have a lot of fillers. It is easy to clean and the ability to drink directly from the blender is a great feature.'),
(3462, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-20', 'Great programable coffee maker Works great. Makes a good pot of coffee. I love the program function.'),
(3463, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-31', 'Five Stars Excellent product, easy to use'),
(3464, 2, 1, 2, '2015-02-23', 'Way too small and gets very hot!! Not what I expected. I have an older black and decker toaster oven and I thought this was the newer version. It is much smaller than my old toaster oven, only has one option for placement of the rack. My old one had two slots for the rack. I used this one time to bake a couple potatoes and it took an hour and a half. Way longer then my old oven. Plus the outside got super hot, way hotter then my old oven. Almost seemed to be dangerous to have it on your countertop. I was going to try and work with it but due to how hot it got on the outside I had to return it. Will just keep my old one until it croaks.'),
(3465, 3, 1, 5, '2015-10-22', 'Does everything a toaster, toaster oven & oven can do in a perfect compact size! Great product!  Purchased this to replace our daughter\'s toaster and toaster oven.  She love it!  It\'s stylish and functional and does everything a toaster, toaster oven and oven can do!  Would purchase again.'),
(3466, 6, 1, 4, '2014-02-11', 'Works Great!! This toaster is perfect for my family.  I have no complaints or issues with this toaster it is as advertised'),
(3467, 3, 1, 2, '2014-07-24', 'Works OK, but door slams to the counter We got this unit as a replacement for a different brand that was over-toasting everything. This one did an OK job of toasting both bread and bagels, and it reheated some pizza using the convection oven setting without any issues. The buttons have good tactile feel, but its a little strange that for the two buttons that increase or decrease settings like temperature, the down arrow is on the right and the up arrow is on the left. I would expect it to be the other way around. There is a major drawback with this unit that caused us to return it. The door has no spring to hold it closed or counter-balance the weight of the very heavy door, so the door wants to fall down to the counter which is very loud every time the handle hits the counter. The door could easily slip out of your hand and crash to the counter, breaking the glass. In addition, the handle hits the counter, and if the door is hot its very hard to get your fingers under it to close it without touching the hot glass. Not very safe! Returned it to Amazon without a hassle due to faulty operation.'),
(3468, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-16', 'Awesome miniature toaster oven Great for cooking almost anything small & convenient, absolutely impressed by all the features!'),
(3469, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-09', 'Great functioning oven with some minor UI flaws. Heats extremely well with many options. It would be nice if there was an extra rack slot closer to the center (vertically) though so that the food does not have to be all the way at the top or the bottom. Also there is no apparent way to set it to back with both the upper and lower elements on at the same time... You have to use \'toast\' to get it to do that in which case you just have a lighter/darker knob with no indication of timing ad no way to just leave it on until you turn it off manually. The other back settings have this, just not the toast or bagel options which is the only way I can find to get both elements to come on.'),
(3470, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-10', 'worth it This is the best coffee maker for the money'),
(3471, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-03', 'energy saver Its small, and it uses less energy than a stove, doesn\'t heat up the whole house, doesn\'t need to be preheated, and is great for quick foods like pizza rolls, stuffed chicken, and other Convenience foods. I love it and its worth every penny.'),
(3472, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-27', 'Five Stars Use it daily.'),
(3473, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-09', 'Good Toaster Oven so far only had this for about 2 weeks so far but this thing is awesome!!! packs alot of punch for a small-ish toaster oven. it looks great with my other black & silver appliances too. my toast comes out super perfect like it should be on a commercial! just dont forget you have to turn all 3 knobs when you want to do something'),
(3474, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-02', 'This oven is greater for toast and broiling. I ... This oven is greater for toast and broiling.  I have not used any of the other features yet. No more burned toast!!!'),
(3475, 3, 1, 4, '2016-06-05', 'Good Oven. First off, it bakes and roasts on convection better than my older convection Jenn-Air oven without heating up the house.  We have roasted a 3# pork loin to perfection, lightly toast pine nuts, and baked cornbread and it did all of them well.  Toast comes out accurately and evenly in a little more time than a slot style toaster.  Melting cheese onto bagels is a breeze.  The buttons feel a little cheap and it wasn\'t super intuitive to figure out, but overall the learning curve was fine.  It replaces a cheaper Black and Decker that lasted a decade or so before a cal-rod burned out.  Sides and top do heat up quite a bit, but this seems very typical of most toaster ovens.'),
(3476, 3, 1, 5, '2015-11-25', 'Very nice little unit Very nice little unit.  Controls are very easy to understand, heats up very quickly, sturdily built.  Good value for the price.'),
(3477, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-13', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(3478, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-10', 'Love this coffee pot Had another brand which finally died.  It also had the removable water container so it could be filled at the sink and popped into the pot.  I found that this was so much neater than trying to pour the water from the top, and possibly getting it all over the counter and the pot.  So, I searched for another one with the removable water container feature.  This one is great; only drawback is it is a bit hard taking it out straight up and putting it back.  Takes a bit of oomph to pull it up and out.  But it doesn\'t leak, period.  Great!'),
(3479, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-15', 'Each Cup perfect! it only makes about two six ounce cups at a time and you\'d have to be right there to put the second cup under.. but I only make one at a time. My daughter home from college for the summer gets up a bit later in the morning, she makes one cup, I make my one cup. NO more wasted coffee! I can\'t tell you how many times I\'ve dumped that unfinished pot. I also LOVE that it has it\'s own permanent filter basket! and it\'s measure for one cup is also perfect! the coffee is the perfect temperature EVERY TIME! there is a small platform that raises and lowers for whatever size mug/cup you\'re using! My favorite on the weekends is Iced coffee... I used to make an entire pitcher, put it in the fridge and then have to throw what was left over on Monday.. Now, I can make it by the cup! No need for expensive pods or packs. It takes 45 seconds max to make a cup... in total maybe a minute and a half and it\'s done. My old coffee pot took twenty minutes and then I had to drag myself about the house waiting for my daily caffeine ... I can\'t say enough about the wonders of this little machine, except I will NEVER part with it!'),
(3480, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-22', 'Just what I was looking for for perfect simple smoothies Just what I was looking for for perfect simple smoothies.  Would not try to put heavy ingredients though, because it is not a heavy duty machine.'),
(3481, 11, 1, 1, '2015-09-08', 'Not ready for prime time. Bought this item just over a year ago...  The shut off timer is no longer working... I\'m lucky that my house didn\'t burn down...  It used to work.. sort of... very uneven toasting and heating... rack design is such that it has no stops so that it tends to drop onto the counter... I would not recommend this item to anyone.'),
(3482, 12, 1, 2, '2014-06-13', 'Hamilton Beach Toastation 22708 I was disappointed because I had the hamilton toaster before and wanted to get the same one, which I did.  However the old version which I ordered, has coils that don\'t heat evenly.  Part of the toast is burned each time I use it.  I can see that the coils have two shades when they a unheated which may account for the difference when they become heated.  I wanted the old model because the tray came out when the door was opened.  I got that, but I did not get the even toast that I had with the previous model.'),
(3483, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-09', 'Problems This product has already quit working.'),
(3484, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-02', 'Great product. So sharp looking on my counter Great product. So sharp looking on my counter. No cheap look or feel to it at all. My first thought was WHO the heck ever needs to warm toast? Well, I\'ve used the reheat feature a few times now, and it really does come in handy.'),
(3485, 1, 1, 1, '2016-08-20', 'Keurig 2.0 the worst kitchen appliance ever I have been a long time Keurig user.  This Keurig 2.0 brewing system is the worst kitchen appliance I have ever owned.  I had two of them in the past 8 months.  My experience was that you had to clean them thoroughly at least once a week (both with the tool provided and also the paperclip technique).  Despite the cleanings, the first unit last less than 6 months and the 2nd unit less than 2 months.  The original Keurig systems were decent, but the 2.0 systems are awful based on my experience.  Three weeks ago we bought the Cuisinart SS-10 and so far it is awesome.  Most important it works without having to clean it multiple times per week.  It is also faster and much quieter and works will all K-cups better than the Keurig 2.0 does.'),
(3486, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-02', 'Five Stars get this one comes with all the things you will need'),
(3487, 12, 1, 3, '2015-11-23', 'It toasts fine, it \"ovens\" ok It toasts fine, it \"ovens\" ok.  The real selling point here is that it has a small footprint and looks decent.  I\'ve been through 2 of them in the last 5-6 years.  In each case, the door mechanism slowly failed and the door wouldn\'t stay closed.  The tray always falls out of position and is extremely annoying, and things you are toasting fall into the over 10% of the time, needing to be pried out.  All that said, I\'m thinking of buying a 3rd because they are relatively inexpensive and, unlike the nicer ones, do not take up a ton of room.'),
(3488, 7, 3, 2, '2016-01-07', 'I got this coffee maker because at the time I didn\'t really want to spend about a $100 on a Keurig. So, I thought I would give this a try. I liked it for a bite. But it took to long to brew my cup. And it also made funky noises that I didn\'t like. So I return it. This product I was a waste of my money. Would recommend this to a friend? NO. If you are looking for a coffee maker: DO NOT get this one. I\'ve said this before IT\'S A WASTE OF YOUR MONEY. If you want a decent product. Give in a get yourself a Keurig.'),
(3489, 2, 1, 1, '2015-05-11', 'It can make toast It will make toast but you are very limited as to what other items you can make in this toaster. We bought it to replace an aging Proctor Silex toaster oven. We should have gone to a store to see the toaster in person. The picture is a bit deceiving in that it seems to have a spacious cooking area, but the rack is very close to the top heating element, and the instructions state you are not to allow whatever you are heating to come within 1 1/2 inches from the top. This poses a problem since there is barely 3 inches clearance between the rack and the element.  Another instruction says you are not to use any foil in the oven. It does not come with any baking tray so this also limits what can be heated. The outside of the unit becomes very hot when in use, and this may be typical, but the handle also gets quite hot. All in all, this is probably our worst purchase from Amazon. We will likely put our old toaster oven back in service, and trash this one.'),
(3490, 5, 1, 4, '2015-06-09', 'Great Coffee. Makes an excellent cup of joe.'),
(3491, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', '8oz cups per day and I have to refill every other day which I am satisfied with. I\'ve had the Keurig for 2 weeks ... To cut expenses from buying coffee out everyday, I decided to buy a Keurig for my office.  Since it will be mostly for myself I chose a K250 2.0 system.  If two or more people are going to being using it, select a model with a larger reservoir.  I brew about 2, 8oz cups per day and I have to refill every other day which I am satisfied with. I\'ve had the Keurig for 2 weeks now and I love being able to make a single cup whenever I want.  A side benefit is the aroma of fresh brewed coffee. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3492, 3, 1, 4, '2014-10-03', 'needs a slight design change to be great Nice toaster oven, works well, BUT it would be nice if the display did a countdown so you could tell how close to done it is. The display just shows the setting it was at when you initiated the operation.'),
(3493, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-28', 'Keurig K250 Brewing System, great product! I love this Keurig! It doesn\'t take up much room and I love the colors! It\'s fast & I love that it holds a lot of water. Great product, I am already recommending it to others. Also, it is easy to use. The touch screen is fun & easy to read.'),
(3494, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-30', 'SO happy with this coffee maker SO happy with this coffee maker.  Less mess than having a carafe.  Love the light over the cup and the empty/full gauge so I know how much I have left.  :)'),
(3495, 12, 1, 5, '2014-02-22', 'Perfection Loving this toaster/oven. Works great and the settings are easily understood. Everyone should consider buying this for their home or office.'),
(3496, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-26', 'works good Very good.'),
(3497, 5, 1, 1, '2016-09-09', 'Head\'s up. Quit working after three brews.'),
(3498, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-14', 'Finally an Amazon appliance that I\'m satisfied with. This is everything I look for in a toaster oven. I can\'t believe it\'s only $30. - The cord is the right length. - It makes a nice dinging sound when my toast is toasted. - The hot bar on the bottom is protected - The knobs and door feel nice and sturdy. The rack and bottom pan were slightly damaged, probably during shipping. I was able to bend them back into shape though.'),
(3499, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-25', 'Great toaster oven but is slightly small... This toaster oven is compact.  It works great to warm up small amount of food or to toast bread. The drawback is that it will not accommodate 8\" Pyrex ware or larger.'),
(3500, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-08', 'What we expected So far very happy.  Toaster oven is exactly what we expected.  Easy to use.'),
(3501, 2, 1, 3, '2015-11-12', 'this is the first time i use it after purchasing ... this is the first time i use it after purchasing. it can become really very hot and you don\'t want to touch it while it is working. while it was working i would stay there to keep watch in fear it would burn itself and so set fire on the kitchen. meanwhile i worry about my safety. to leave or not to leave, that is the question. it also diffuse a smell of burnt rubber. i will see'),
(3502, 10, 1, 3, '2015-01-05', 'just so so nice look but less functionality than expected'),
(3503, 9, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'Five Stars Makes the best coffee and it\'s so easy to use.'),
(3504, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'It is easy to set the doneness Friends who live on the East Coast (we are in Seattle) raved about their toaster.  So we bought one.  It works perfectly.  We actually donated our toaster oven which never worked very well and took up more room.  It is easy to set the doneness.  I especially like the loud ding so you butter the toast before it cools.  We bought red which looks spiffy with our red Kitchen Aid mixer.'),
(3505, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-16', 'Love this. Works great in either position Just bought my second one.  Love this.  Works great in either position.  Use as a pop up toaster or slide the lever to close off the toaster slots and use as a toaster oven for melting cheese on bread, warming pizza, etc...'),
(3506, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-15', 'Five Stars Works well all the way around.'),
(3507, 6, 1, 3, '2016-05-11', 'Three Stars Grate for the price.'),
(3508, 2, 1, 2, '2016-06-20', 'Much too complex. Dial lettering/numbers are much too small ... Much too complex.  Dial lettering/numbers are much too small.'),
(3509, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-02', 'We got this for our daughter. It is a terrific machine! We have a mr coffee single brew & a Kerig also in our family. This Hamilton beach flex bre is awesome!!!!'),
(3510, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-19', 'Five Stars I waited to post a listing for product performance  great little oven  works just fine'),
(3511, 11, 1, 4, '2016-08-02', 'Four Stars Works fine.'),
(3512, 2, 1, 3, '2016-04-29', 'I don\'t like how I have to wait for the timer to ... I guess for something this cheap, it\'s what you get. I saw some smoke coming from the handle when I put it at toast mode, which I think sets it to max temperature. I don\'t like how I have to wait for the timer to complete for the oven to turn off, but like I said, for something this cheap, it\'s not too bad, but I seriously doubt the safety features on it.'),
(3513, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-10', 'Nice toaster for the price works well. a little confusing at first to turn on the toaster by turning the knob past burnt, and then back to the desired setting. heats up fast and does the job.'),
(3514, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-27', 'Five Stars Use this just about every day to make fruit smoothies.'),
(3515, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-01', 'LOVE this coffee maker! Best coffee maker we have ever owned.  No issues with any of the features, and it keeps the coffee hot for a very long time.  Its such a great product at an affordable price!'),
(3516, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-14', 'Four Stars missing the tray pull out hook.'),
(3517, 9, 1, 1, '2015-03-29', 'Serious mold issues between unsealed walls of coffee holder. Okay, I\'ve had this for a while now. I see major, MAJOR flaws. It is cheaply constructed, not worth the money. They were considerate enough to think of double walled construction on the carafe..or the part(s) that hold the coffee (most likely for insulation). Unfortunately they did not SEAL the double walls, which allows moisture to collect between the walls. From my point of view...since it is not sealed...I have mold growing between the 2 UNSEALED walls. Geez, you would think any engineer who designed this would know better.'),
(3518, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-20', 'Five Stars Great toaster. A bit large but it looks good on the counter.'),
(3519, 9, 1, 4, '2017-01-14', 'I thought is was a very smart design, though difficult to send in the warranty My sister has the same machine.  I thought is was a very smart design, though difficult to send in the warranty; couldn\'t locate the # or paperwork with it.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(3520, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love it! This is my first Keurig and I love it! I don\'t drink coffee on a regular basis so it\'s nice to just have a cup here and there. It\'s easy to use and quick! I saw some people complain about the noise. I don\'t think it\'s that loud. It keeps some water preheated all the time so it makes a cup instantly. I love the color as well! It doesn\'t really match my other appliances, but who has all turquoise appliances?! It\'s still super cute though!'),
(3521, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-19', 'Five Stars Bought for my daughter and she loves it!'),
(3522, 5, 1, 1, '2014-05-13', 'Display Fell Apart Within Months As a coffee maker, this unit was fine - it made a pretty decent cup of coffee. That being said, this is a fairly significant design flaw with this machine:  Steam easily escapes from the front of the door housing the filter/coffee, and makes its way into the display.  Over time, the display not only becomes filled with condensation, but also becomes weakened.  The plastic literally fell apart within months, and the face plate for the display panel literally fell off, with buttons going one by one over time. I\'ve since replaced this unit with a simple Bunn, which is much more simple and in its own class. Note:  This coffee maker does have a 1 year warranty, which this defect would be covered by.  That being said, Hamilton Beach wants the consumer to pay for return shipping of the defective unit, as well as the shipping of the new unit...you might as well buy another coffee maker.'),
(3523, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-16', 'thank you for this perfect coffee pot Hamilton Beach..thank you for this perfect coffee pot. It makes great coffee, and we love all the features! I have been looking for the best coffee maker for a couple months. The last coffee pot we bought was a Hamilton Beach as well, and that\'s s the first time I\'ve been moved to take the time to thank a company for manufacturing such a great product. That machine lasted many years and we were disappointed when it stopped working. But we were thrilled to find this one, which has several improvements! Highly recommend!'),
(3524, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-18', 'Good value. Compact and just right for cooking for one. Good value.'),
(3525, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-13', 'Five Stars Nice little toaster for the price.'),
(3526, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-01', 'Great Toaster Nice toaster, lots of room in each slot, has mighty fine features that I like. Defrost for one of them. I like to use this toaster for my hash brown patties.'),
(3527, 12, 1, 2, '2015-11-01', 'I was quite disappointed when the heating element in the oven portion ceased ... I was quite disappointed when the heating element in the oven portion ceased working after only three uses (reheating croissants and tartines).  While the toaster continued to work, I found that it had to be watched rather carefully in that the heating settings did not appear to be accurate for my purposes.  I would not buy another.'),
(3528, 4, 1, 1, '2016-12-15', 'NOT WORTH A SLICE OF BREAD NOT WORTH A PENNY NOT THE COST OF A SLICE OF BREAD We bought this Cuisinart Oven/Broiler in August 2013. We bought the Cuisinart brand (even though it was a little more expensive) because almost all of our small home appliances are Cuisinart. In fact, yesterday we celebrated 42 years of marriage, and we still have our 42-year old Cuisinart food processor that travelled with us to four different South American countries! Cuisinart has never failed us once, except with their oven/broiler we bought. The on/off switch just stopped working. This is very disappointing for my husband who is an Executive Chef at a 4-star restaurant. He liked using the oven/broiler for home use. But getting only 2-1/2 years out of an appliance that only kept food warm and toasted bread, is outrageous.  I am very disappointed with this purchase, so if you\'re looking to buy one, be careful and know your money will be washed down the drain. We\'ll be buying a simple Black & Decker!.'),
(3529, 12, 1, 3, '2014-08-27', 'Three Stars This toaster is great except the power cord is so short!  Wish it had a normal length cord :('),
(3530, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'Very easy to use and I have had no problems Fits in with my retro kitchen perfectly. Very easy to use and I have had no problems.'),
(3531, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-28', 'Five Stars still works great, bought this a long time ago from amazon..'),
(3532, 1, 1, 1, '2016-01-27', 'Fails miserably on several fronts. Got this as a Christmas present thinking this was going to be a nice addition to our kitchen, allowing my wife and I to have a single cup whenever we want. Boy, was I wrong! Followed all setup instructions to the letter, first brew or two went fine, although the flavor of the coffees themselves were thin, weak, watery, poor excuse for a proper cup of coffee. We played with the \"strong\" setting, but it only helped marginally. By the time we had gotten to the fourth or fifth brew we started to get the \"Sorry, there is a problem\" error message on screen. Cleaned the needle as per instructions and we were back in business. Or so I thought. We constantly went back and forth between being able to make either one cup or coffee, or dispense hot water, to error message and repeating cleaning process. Over, and over. What was particularly annoying was that we had used K-Cups for 2.0 and still got error messages, cleaned it frequently and basically had a non-functioning piece of \"counter sculpture\" (which incidentally takes up quite a bit of space) more often than we had a bad tasting coffee maker. No hassle return processed by Amazon allowed us to ship it back. Maybe ours had a glitch, even so: if this product had worked more frequently I still would not be happy with the flavor and strength of the coffee it makes. We tried several brands, roasts of coffee. Nothing ever tasted good.'),
(3533, 4, 1, 2, '2015-12-11', 'Not a good thing. I through with Cuisinart First one burnt toast.  The one I have now - a little over a year - not only burns toast but the front bottom heating coil is collapsing and touching the crumb tray and sparks.  Not a good thing.  I through with Cuisinart.  Looking at other manufacturers.'),
(3534, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-23', 'Krazy for Keurig Debbie Wilcher Just now  Amazon  I love my single cup coffee maker it is so perfect for me. Hot or Cold drinks... Its awesome! This is my third one and I plan on getting the new KOLD brewer. Thanx Keurig. Sincerely Debbie Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing System, Black So many choices. So Simple. So Delicious. The Keurig 2.0 K250 Brewing System features revolutionary Keurig 2.0 Brewing Technology , designed to read the lid of each K-Cup or K-Carafe pack to brew the perfect beverage every time. Theres even... amazon.com'),
(3535, 8, 1, 2, '2016-02-13', 'TOO SMALL ONLY MAKES 5 CUPS..... PAY ATTENTION TO DETAILS!!!'),
(3536, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-15', 'Nice toaster, a little expensive Nice toaster, no complaints. Seems to toast evenly and holds bagels well. Certainly expensive for something as simple as a toaster, but it is good quality.'),
(3537, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-22', 'great so far So far it works great!  I like that the water tank is removable so that you can fill it up directly, rather than having to pour it into the actual coffee machine.'),
(3538, 9, 1, 3, '2016-03-01', 'Coffee good but WARNING  has a stubby 6\" cord I bought this because I cracked the water resivour in my last one.  Although it make coffee well (hence the reason I\'m replacing the same model), the freakin cord that use to be 22\" is now Is 6\".  I had to buy a 2\" high stand just to reach the outlet that is directly behind it. Now everytime I want to make a new pot,  I have to unplug it, which of course then resets the clock.  I don\'t get why they\'d do that.  The directions mention using an extension cord with it, but this is a replacement.  Why would i have to buy an additional extension cord when I didn\'t the 1st time?  I went thru a lot of trouble to select the coffee pot the 1st time.  Very disappointing.  Had I know that I would have chosen a different one.'),
(3539, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-04', 'Love My Hamilton Beach 12 Cup Digital Coffee Maker This is my first Hamilton Beach Coffee Maker and I love it! I was so tired of more expensive, other brands, that were designed to dispense one cup at a time, leaking all over my counter. This one is perfect for me, easy to operate, and takes up minimal space on my counter..'),
(3540, 5, 1, 2, '2016-04-12', 'Front plate broke. Front plate fell off after 30 days, and the electronics now slide in and out...not very safe I\'m sure; and the water basin leaks.  Unable to replace per policy, as I\'ve had longer than 30 days.  I like how hot the coffee is with this maker, I think I must have gotten a defective machine.'),
(3541, 2, 1, 2, '2015-04-20', 'At least it works but I can not figure why ... At least it works but I can not figure why it got such a high rating. Must be the cheap price. Dial setting requires a magnifying glass to read and you have to turn the dial past the 10 minute mark and then return it to the time you want.'),
(3542, 3, 1, 5, '2014-07-06', 'Just what we needed. Yes this item met or exceeded all expectations, we liked it so much we bought another one to give as an anniversary present.'),
(3543, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-12', 'Five Stars Works well!'),
(3544, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-16', 'Love this coffee pot! So far this is my favorite coffee pot. I love that the water unit comes off in the back. So easy to fill. No pouring water into the unit which is awesome! I also love that my coffee no longer has that burnt taste when it sits for more than an hour. My coffee actually still tastes good after I drop my daughter off after school! Very easy to clean. Nice compact unit that doesn\'t take up much counter space. I owned this for almost a year and so far no issues with anything.'),
(3545, 4, 1, 2, '2016-09-25', 'Great Toaster, for the first 2 years... Like many on here, I liked the toaster at first... It worked well and served its purpose. However, around 2 years in the heating element on the bottom warped. I still used it, but the door also became harder and harder to open. As of today, I could only open it about 1/3 if the way, forcing me to reach into a hot toaster to try to pull things out. I was going to buy a new one, but saw my old order on Amazon and discovered it was still under warranty. I\'m hoping I have better luck with the new one. I have to say Customer Service was helpful and gave no argument about sending me out a replacement. I do have to send $10 and the cord back in (I guess to prove I\'m not using the old one). Still, $10 is cheaper than buying a new toaster oven so I\'m giving it a second chance.'),
(3546, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-10', 'Great maker so far i love this maker. makes a good cup of coffe. the only dissapointment is it doesnt have a bell telling when its done & turning off. i love the removeable water tank & wheels to move it around. if you dont want to take the tank off to fill you can leave it in the pot & fill using the crafe. that\'s what i do. but being able to remove tank for cleaning is priceless. it would the perfect maker for me if it just had a finish bell.'),
(3547, 9, 1, 3, '2015-03-08', 'I can\'t seem to get away from having coffee grounds ... I can\'t seem to get away from having coffee grounds in my coffee whenever I make coffee with the coffee maker...'),
(3548, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-18', 'The item is great even if it did arrive with a dent in ... The item is great even if it did arrive with a dent in the handle.  I wasn\'t able to return it as I had company coming and needed it.  So except for the dent when it arrived the item works well.'),
(3549, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-15', 'Customer service terrible. I will never purchase Cuisinart brand again Do not buy! Safety hazard! Defective heating element. Customer service terrible. I will never purchase Cuisinart brand again.'),
(3550, 4, 1, 3, '2016-08-26', 'This toaster oven does a great job toasting and baking This toaster oven does a great job toasting and baking, heats up quickly and cooks evenly.  Downfall...no timer when baking or broiling.  I have to set a separate kitchen timer to remind me to check on my food. I didn\'t know this when I made the purchase.  It\'s easy to overcook or burn food without a built-in timer.'),
(3551, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-20', 'Great CoffeeMaker! Love this coffee maker...very quiet....makes tasty coffee...love the removeable water container. Takes up very little space in kitchen. Love it!'),
(3552, 9, 1, 1, '2016-04-18', 'Beautiful Mess Can\'t trust the maker.  Following the instructions doesn\'t help. The reservoir valve will clog up with grounds and your maker will run out over your counter and floor.  Took special pains to follow the exact procedures in the manual but just when you think you have it down you will goof to work and come home with a mess.  Design problem.'),
(3553, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-08', 'This is the best coffee maker I have ever owned This is the best coffee maker I have ever owned. Easy to operate easy to clean,that was very important.'),
(3554, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-19', 'Four Stars East to use.'),
(3555, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Love love love! Just bought the 2.0 Keurig brewer and I love it! It holds water in the back and is super easy to use. I especially love the fact that you can chose the size of your cup to brew from 4, 6, or 10 oz size and also had the capability of the carafe. I cannot say enough good things about this and will be buying the brand again. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(3556, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'Great product for a variety of cooking needs So far this toaster oven has worked well for us!'),
(3557, 6, 1, 1, '2014-11-17', 'One Star Do not buy. This is not a toaster it is a burner. Does not work for toast'),
(3558, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-05', 'Five Stars We love this coffee maker!!!  Improved from previous model.'),
(3559, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-03', 'Very easy to use and clean Very easy to use and clean! Love that I can auto-program to brew coffee and program time frame to keep warm! I had a keurig prior to this Cuisinart coffee maker and would highly recommend this if shopping for a coffee maker.'),
(3560, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-25', 'Five Stars I love the removable water tank in the back.'),
(3561, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-13', 'Really a good toaster Good product.  Great way to buy.'),
(3562, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-30', 'OVERPRICED Overpriced. No timer. Much better value toaster ovens out there.'),
(3563, 2, 1, 1, '2016-03-21', 'I love the look of the toaster oven I love the look of the toaster oven, but mine did not come with a removable tray. Without the tray, I cannot use the product.'),
(3564, 5, 1, 4, '2015-09-07', 'Great Coffee Maker I recently purchased this coffee maker and it\'s been wonderful. I can program it to make til 12 cups. No leaks and great for brewing my concoction. I can smell the aroma of the coffee unlike my other coffee maker it rarely smell the aroma.'),
(3565, 9, 1, 1, '2016-11-06', 'One Star This coffee maker is leaking, need to send back please give me instructions!.'),
(3566, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-27', 'LOVE Love it so much. Easy to use. It has a water filter in it. I love the color choices. I can also choose small cup size to thermos and there is an option to add strength to the brew. I cant think of anything bad about it. Ive had it for a month.'),
(3567, 5, 1, 4, '2016-05-09', 'yet This coffee maker brews really good coffee, especially on the \"bold\" setting Still gave this thing 4 stars, even though the first one ordered died less than a week after receiving it. Just went dead during the night...no power, no lit display, and no coffee...on a Monday morning of all days, lol. Return & replacement was hassle free. Have not had any problems with the second one...yet This coffee maker brews really good coffee, especially on the \"bold\" setting.  The warmer plate keeps the coffee really hot. No problems with the pause & serve. Brew time is about average for regular brew (10 min.) and about 15 min. for bold. Very easy to clean up. Have had no problems with face plate as others have mentioned. Programming is simple and straightforward. Access to the water reservoir is made easy due to the wheels on the back end. Very happy with this product as long as it does continue to function.'),
(3568, 3, 1, 5, '2014-08-12', 'ham sandwich Be careful if you have kids as the outside gets very hot and I got burned pretty good the other day.  I can take it though as i am young man still in my 20s.  It heats up fast.  The coils inside seem pretty solid.  The pan is pretty good quality too,  The timer is kinda dinky as it simply beeps once, but the oven turns off after that so you are ok.'),
(3569, 8, 1, 1, '2016-08-15', 'looks like used one The packaging was awful, looks like used one. I don\'t recommend this one, waste of money.'),
(3570, 11, 1, 4, '2014-03-30', 'great toaster oven for the price It\'s a great toaster oven for the price if you\'re buying it online, but my parents bought it for cheaper at macy\'s, so I would suggest keeping a spare eye out for in store sales. Also be aware that the top of the toaster oven gets REALLY hot when it is on so don\'t put things on top of it that might melt easily if you forget them.'),
(3571, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-19', 'makes better coffee than our old one We switched from the cone filter to the basket and I was worried it wouldn\'t be as strong ... makes better coffee than our old one! I guess I should have switched sooner.'),
(3572, 2, 1, 2, '2015-09-11', 'The controls on this unit are terrible. You only need to turn the knob about ... The controls on this unit are terrible. You only need to turn the knob about 15 degrees to get something toasted but the knob turns 270 degrees, I dont know who is turning it that far? Then if you try to turn it off manually and go too far it stays on for ever. Really bad controls, I definitely would not buy again.'),
(3573, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-10', 'I expected better! We bought this item 2 years ago. All went well...until today.  The bottom heating element warped so badly the bottom tray was burned.  Not good-especially at the price paid.  I\'ll go back to a regular toaster...shame on you Cuisinart, I expected better!'),
(3574, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-08', 'This thing must hate toast, because every time I try it\'s burnt ... Works on everything but toast. This thing must hate toast, because every time I try it\'s burnt to hell in a few minutes.'),
(3575, 5, 1, 2, '2016-05-01', 'Cuisinart coffee machines make much better coffee We\'ve had this coffee maker for about a year and a half now and it\'s starting to die. It seems that once the water level in the reservoir reaches 2 cups, it has difficulty pumping the remainder out. The coffee has never been very good. We switched from Cuisinart to this one after 3 Cuisinarts burned up right after the warranty was up but the Cuisinarts always produced much better tasting coffee. Needless to say, we\'re going back to Cuisinart. We thought we\'d give this one a try so we didn\'t have to keep spending $100 on coffee machines every year or so but this one hasn\'t lasted much longer.'),
(3576, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-09', 'Great product Works great. Came fast.'),
(3577, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-14', 'Good for reheating foods I was able to reheat the leftover foods at home ever since I started using this thing.'),
(3578, 12, 1, 5, '2015-08-15', 'Love it! Great purchase! We love this little toaster/oven we love that it\'s a combo and doesn\'t take up much space. We mostly use it for warming items since we don\'t eat a lot of processed food and it warms it quickly and efficiently. The only minor con I\'ve noticed is at toast setting 4 it toasts the top visibly more than the bottom half of the bread. It doesn\'t bother me but it may some.'),
(3579, 12, 1, 4, '2015-03-03', '... an ugly retro tan color rather than all silver like it looks in the picture In person it\'s kind of an ugly retro tan color rather than all silver like it looks in the picture, but other than that it\'s great! The slot fits a whole bagel as pictures and the toaster gets nice and hot.'),
(3580, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-05', 'LOVE IT. Yes LOVE IT. Yes, it gets hot. It has warning labels on top telling you it gets hot. Its an oven. Other than that it is great.'),
(3581, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-22', 'I\'ve had it for little over a month and a ... For the super cheap price, it works really well. Not the greatesttoaster oven but will do for now.'),
(3582, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Five Stars Fast delivery, product as described.'),
(3583, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-10', 'Outstanding tool Outstanding tool. I have made muffins, pizzas, cornbread, and all kinds of meats in this oven.  I would recommend this to any of my family.'),
(3584, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-11', 'Superbly Adequate Toaster It\'s a reasonably priced toaster. Makes good toast. Replaced the broken toaster. What more can I say?'),
(3585, 5, 1, 3, '2016-04-26', 'it sounds like the coffee maker is sparking I\'ve used this coffee maker 3 times. The basket is already broken and when the coffee is sitting, it sounds like the coffee maker is sparking. Not sure how I feel. Overall the build and convenience of the item is great.'),
(3586, 7, 3, 1, '2016-06-25', 'Need to return it leaks'),
(3587, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-28', 'Four Stars I like it a lot but it seems to be very loud and struggles to brew my coffee'),
(3588, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-14', 'Five Stars Perfect for two people!  Love it.'),
(3589, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-21', 'Five Stars Works very good and delivery service was fine.'),
(3590, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-22', 'Love mine, have it at my office. You can put a larger container in and fill it up.'),
(3591, 7, 3, 1, '2016-02-24', 'This is the second machine I have had and both times it quits pumping right after the 90-day return window. Regular cleaning and maintenance did not help. When calling customer service they want an additional $20 for shipping out a new machine...why bother when you just have to pay an additional $20 in 3 months again. Very poor product and poor customer service'),
(3592, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-20', 'Coffee Delicious! We are very happy with this product. Although it\'s been only two weeks, our device performs perfectly, as in, ease of use, programming, filling water reservoir, & the button control coffee basket opener allows the device to stay put on the counter. The coffee pot is designed not to drip after pouring & it works perfectly, too. We use paper filters & no grounds have gone into the coffee. I like the wheels, too. No issue cleaning around it. The price was very reasonable & a good value. I bought this product based on a number of excellent reviews & I am providing my feedback to support them. They were right!'),
(3593, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-24', 'Nice coffee maker with a few improvements needed! I like this coffee maker but the light which indicates the time is way too bright and lights up a dark room.  Also, there is no beep when the coffee is done.  I also wish it was 14 cups, not 12.  Those considerations aside, it makes good coffee and the fact that it swivels for easily getting to the water container are a plus.'),
(3594, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-11', 'Five Stars We love it and the toast is made evenly and just the way we like it.'),
(3595, 2, 1, 2, '2016-04-02', 'Not particularly pleased with this purchase Not particularly pleased with this purchase.  I was hoping with the brand name of Black and Decker that it would be a good one.  But it cooks very unevenly and tends to burn either the toast, waffles or bagels.  Not a great purchase'),
(3596, 3, 1, 5, '2014-09-07', 'Wonderful toaster oven Now this is a toaster oven! We had a crappy one before this that I hated and my husband bought this one. Is so sturdy and I love all of the functions! It\'s nice to have a toaster that actually toasts!'),
(3597, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-01', 'Bagel Toaster This toaster is great. Settings for lots of types of breads. I use the bagel setting quite often. You can add time to the setting if it isn\'t quite right.'),
(3598, 5, 1, 4, '2016-06-20', 'Great Good coffee maker.'),
(3599, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-14', 'THE BEST TOASTER EVER! Love this toaster...the best toaster I have ever used!.'),
(3600, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-27', 'I really like having the removable water reservoir as well as the ... At first glance, the actual coffee maker felt too light and flimsy, but after using for a few weeks, it\'s hardly noticeable. Though, I really like having the removable water reservoir as well as the front loading brew basket and the functions that allow me to control the warming temperature. I\'ll just have to see if it holds up over the long term. Considered getting the filters for it but not seeing great reviews.'),
(3601, 6, 1, 4, '2014-01-05', 'I\'m only giving it 4 stars because it\'s white It works great!  Toasts all kinds of bread, bagels, etc. very evenly.  Easy enough to clean (for a toaster).  But it\'s white... 2nd worst color for a kitchen appliance (next to black, of course).'),
(3602, 3, 1, 4, '2015-09-10', 'Nice Unit. The unit was a bit larger than I expected (bulkier) but it is a great unit.  I love that full pizzas can fit and it bakes pretty well also.  We have so far been pleased.'),
(3603, 9, 1, 4, '2015-01-30', 'Four Stars the filter system improves the taste of the coffee since the water here is hard.'),
(3604, 2, 1, 3, '2016-07-06', 'Good for toasting and baking frozen food, timer stops working, bad spring As an oven it works just fine. The timer stopped working after a couple of uses. Since it\'s a mechanical timer, I\'m guessing the mechanism wasn\'t built very durable. So now it won\'t turn off after you set the time on the timer. It seems like the timer doesn\'t have a very strong spring or something. You\'ll need to use a separate timer and stop the oven yourself. It comes with a drip pan which is useful to keep the oven clean. It would have been nice for the rack to pull out when you open the door with some sort of hook to pull the small rack out. It heats up much faster than a full size kitchen oven, so it is more convenient to heat up frozen food with it vs the microwave which doesn\'t taste as good.'),
(3605, 6, 1, 1, '2014-10-26', 'One Star this toaster toasts darker on one side'),
(3606, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-31', 'So in love with the color So in love with the color, its way brighter in person. works great - have it on my desk in my office.'),
(3607, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'Best coffee maker I have owned. Makes excellent tasting coffee. Internal reservoir keeps hot but not burnt. Dispensing system eliminates broken carafes.'),
(3608, 4, 1, 4, '2015-09-08', 'Four Stars It\'s exactly what I expected'),
(3609, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-02', 'Pass on this one This toaster is the worst. One side of the bread will be almost burt and the other side will barely be toasted. The setting dial is so loose, that if you happen to touch it while getting it out, the settings change. You can\'t get a nicely toasted piece of bread with this toaster no matter how many settings you try, Both sides are bad. I don\'t even think I will wait until it breaks to get rid of it. I thought Cuisinart was a good brand, not so in this case.'),
(3610, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Five Stars Only one we found that didn\'t make annoying \"clicking\" noise while toasting.  Does everything well.'),
(3611, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', '... first Keurig a couple of weeks ago and I love it! Since my husband and I have different ... Received my first Keurig a couple of weeks ago and I love it!  Since my husband and I have different coffee tastes I was having to use two coffee pots.  Now I can make myself a single cup of coffee from several different k-cups to choose from and my husband can make his pot of coffee (using the carafe) from coffee grinds he prefers.  Everyone is happy..wished I would have bought one sooner!  Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(3612, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Love my new Keurig with the carafe We are very pleased with the function of our new Keurig brewing system.  This is our third one and love the convenience of being able to make just one cup of coffee and very quickly.  This machine is a little louder than our previous one\'s but hopefully will continue to work without problems for a long time in the future. I think we are committed to Keurig brewers from now on. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(3613, 10, 1, 2, '2015-04-19', 'Toothless. Can\'t recommend it. This might be the worst piece of kitchen equipment I may have bought that I have regretted not returning right away. The only reason it\'s not a 1-star review is because of the jar and lid doubling as a personal cup. That\'s a neat feature. This blender has almost no power. Running for any duration more than pulsing smells like burning plastic. And it won\'t even chafe ice cubes, let alone blend them. If all you want is to crush soft stuff like bananas and berries, go for it. But anything remotely harder than that, and you are out of luck.'),
(3614, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-23', 'Great for the money Perfect size and easy to grab and go! Only downfall is, I have to continuously stir so the top contents makes it down to the blades. But for the price, it\'s a great buy.'),
(3615, 4, 1, 4, '2016-11-06', 'Four Stars Basic, all-purpose toaster oven does the trick. But a word of caution: the outside gets very hot.'),
(3616, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Great! Very nice for the price and use it regularly. Had it several months now.'),
(3617, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-09', 'Five Stars Great toaster!.'),
(3618, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', 'It turned out to be awesome from 2 reasons I was suspicious when I bought this blender. It turned out to be awesome from 2 reasons: 1- my cousin saw it and she said this is a great blender I had same as this one like it and I still have since 2010 2- I blend ice, water, powerder and that\'s all I need and they give me a great smoothie. besides, it\'s not loud, easy to clean, the only hard part to clean is the cover since it has some narrow places that the sponge may not reach, but that is not a big issue for me. I totally recommend it it\'s worth it, it\'s affordable'),
(3619, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-10', 'better breakfast with the toaster oven This product make my breakfast better in every morning :D Like it so much!!'),
(3620, 4, 1, 5, '2016-09-19', 'Five Stars Love that you don\'t have to listen to a timer tick down!.'),
(3621, 11, 1, 5, '2015-05-07', 'just got it seems to be good havent used it just got it seems to be good havent used it enough'),
(3622, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-07', 'Five Stars As pictured'),
(3623, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-23', 'It\'s perfect. I use this for my polymer clay business. It\'s perfect.'),
(3624, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-29', 'Great toaster oven. This is a great toaster oven. I know you could pay more for one, but why would you when this one does such a great job?  It looks nice on my countertop and has all of the features we need. My kids love to use it to make little batches of cookies, or to toast little pizzas for an after school snack. You can\'t go wrong with choosing this one. Just beware of the settings or you may burn your toast.'),
(3625, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-26', 'Makes a great cup of coffee with minimal clean up I\'ve owned two Cuisanart coffee makers in the past (both Grind & Brews) and this maker is just as good, if not a bit better from a cleaning perspective. Just empty the gold tone filter and wash with warm soapy water and you\'re done. The fact that there isn\'t a carafe is kind of genius. Having owned two Keurigs over the past few years, I grew tired of the K-Cups and really craved a good old-fashioned cup of coffee. You\'re going to get that with this machine. The design is quite beautiful and I love how it lights up your coffee as you pour into your mug. Those familiar with Cuisanart will probably like that the machine has similar features to the other models, including the five gentle beeps it makes after completing the brew cycle. It takes about 7 minutes to brew a full 12 cups. I brew about 2 cups daily and this model is perfect for that. Easy to set the night before, brews quickly, gives off a nice aroma, and clean up is minimal. Regarding commuter mugs: I use the Oxo Good Grips stainless steel mug and it fits under the machine after you remove the drip tray. If you have anything taller, it\'s not going to fit unless you angle the mug under the pour spout. The reviewers who complained about the electric cord being too short don\'t realize that you need to tug firmly when you first remove from the box. The cord is exactly the length stated in the product description. A gentle yank should do the trick. See my photo for reference. Although I do love the minimal parts and effort to clean after using, I would like to see another model like this with the Grind & Brew option. I am a big fan of that model because you don\'t have to use a separate device to grind the beans. But, you go into it knowing you have to clean the grinding chamber and its lid daily (hence why two less parts to clean on this model is attractive, in addition to not cleaning a carafe and lid daily). Overall this is a fantastic machine for those tired of the K-Cups, Nespresso pods, etc., but want a similar machine using \"normal coffee.\"'),
(3626, 12, 1, 5, '2014-01-07', 'good idea I love the toastation.  It allows you to use it as a pop up toaster and then also as a toasteroven!  Great idea'),
(3627, 6, 1, 4, '2016-12-18', 'This Toaster Lasted Four Years I bought this toaster in December of 2012. Then it was $29.00. It no longer works. Now it is $25.00. Not a bad toaster that was used every day for 4 years for the money. I\'ll buy another one. I rated it 4 stars because it would have been great if it lasted longer!.'),
(3628, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-08', 'I\'ve been using the coffee maker for about a week or so and absolutely love it. It\'s ready to use right out of the box, and can be used with a coffee cup (using the included stand) or a travel mug. I really enjoy the flexibility of being able to either use ground coffee or k-cups. It doesn\'t take up much counter space and has auto shut-off, which is another nice feature. I\'ve read reviews from others about the coffee maker shooting water/coffee all over the place. I have not encountered this at all. Also, I\'ve used k-cups and a medium ground coffee and have had no problems with clogging or with grounds in my coffee cup. I will still keep my 12 cup coffee maker for days when at home or have company, but this single cup brew coffee maker is great when I want only want a single cup of coffee or as I head out to work. Normally I would just wait until I got to work for my first cup of coffee. With this product, I take a travel mug of coffee with me every day as I head out. No need to bother with the 12 cup coffee maker. Great product! I would definitely recommend it.'),
(3629, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-18', 'Easy to clean I like the removable tray that allows for VERY easy cleaning of this toaster. Great for my first apartment/very light cooking needs.'),
(3630, 6, 1, 3, '2015-02-25', 'Pretty Standard This toaster works pretty good.  Nothing to rave about.'),
(3631, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-14', 'EXCELENTE PRODUCTO EXCELENTE PRODUCTO'),
(3632, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-07', 'Four Stars BETTER CONTROLS WOUD BE HELPFUL OR A DIFFERENT ARRANGEMENT'),
(3633, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'one of the best inexpensive toaster ovens available I bought this for home on deal of the day which was around $20 less th an the going price, but before this, I also ordered one for work at full price and I thought that was a deal!  It\'s used on a regular basis and it works well.  The other toaster ovens I read reviews on had little issues like the glass shattering or no safety shutoff.  This one just works.  I would pay full asking price for it.'),
(3634, 3, 1, 3, '2016-07-16', 'Not great Not as good as I was expecting. Takes a long time to cook even frozen french fries. Tried to cook pork chops in it after 45 min. they were still raw I then had to use my large oven to finish the job.'),
(3635, 4, 1, 2, '2017-01-18', 'This Cuisinart was the perfect fit and the style was just right This Cuisinart was the perfect fit and the style was just right!  The heat that this toaster oven emitted was insane!  The possibility of getting burned by just touching the glass or the top of the oven...very likely.  A possible fire starter.  Returned the same day I received product.'),
(3636, 12, 1, 4, '2014-01-25', 'Does the job It is the perfect size for two people.  I like that I can toast a longer, thicker piece of bread.  It does not toast evenly but it is OK.  I can make tuna melts, or toasted left over biscuits, etc.  For the cost, it is a lot of toaster.'),
(3637, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-05', 'Five Stars it has various settings bagel, defrost, reheat and cancel'),
(3638, 1, 1, 3, '2016-02-06', 'Three Stars could use a larger reservoir, especially when using 10 OZ.'),
(3639, 4, 1, 1, '2016-12-07', 'Returned Returned did not need.'),
(3640, 5, 1, 3, '2015-04-03', 'jst wat expected Best coffee maker we have ever owned. No issues with any of the features, and it keeps the coffee hot for a very long time.'),
(3641, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-06', 'Gets a bad smell when it tries to do this almost as ... Won\'t even crunch up ice. Gets a bad smell when it tries to do this almost as it\'s burning'),
(3642, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-08', 'I love it! I love it!! I use it to Blend all my fruit at works and it blends it so well'),
(3643, 10, 1, 4, '2016-01-26', 'Four Stars Love it for a quick smoothie on the go!'),
(3644, 2, 1, 1, '2016-06-19', 'Not recommended for small spaces or for homes with children and ... Outer body of appliance gets dangerously hot rapidly. Inner elements are amazingly ineffective  - toaster and baking functions inexplicably slow. Not recommended for small spaces or for homes with children and pets.'),
(3645, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-28', 'Five Stars Love it, it\'s so easy to fill the tank with water & convenient.'),
(3646, 9, 1, 1, '2015-10-07', 'Not enough user acceptaance testing performed!!!!!  Nice looking but has quirks and needs improvement. Not enough user acceptaance testing performed!!!!!  Okay I have had this thing since May of 2014.  It looks nice.  It\'s retro.  It\'s woman and physically challenged people friendly.  I bought this after exhaustive research and stealth in-store testing on coffee makers that don\'t require a lot of arm strength to pour a cup of coffee.  So this thing, you can pour the water in with good arm (in my case left, and I am right-dominant), fill the little filter with coffe,  and when the coffee is ready, VOILA you put the cup under the spigot and press the lever.  I\'ve been really careful about setting the coffee basket like 100% plumb and 100% level like I was setting a door or window.  Well, I got the infamous \"coffee leaks seriously, like big-time, onto countertop\" experience.  Many times.  Despite re-orienting the coffee basket, saying prayers, whatever it took, well, I got coffee all over the place.  Not good.  So when this thing DOES work WITHOUT making a tsunami of brown water on my countertops, the coffee is NOT hot.  Now I don\'t mean this to infer that I want coffee so hot it burns my tongue off and maybe my teeth too.  But coffee hot enough so that when my beloved half -n-half gets poured it, it will last me for a ride down the road for more than 5 minutes before turning into an iced latte.  Oh so let\'s talk about down the road.  I suppose these engineers NEVER thought, well, maybe, perhaps, one day, someone might maybe want to actually TAKE their coffee to work with them!  Lukewarm or not, I don\'t personally know anyone that drives to work using a 6 ounce go-cup.  The issue is - this thing IS NOT TALL ENOUGH to shove a 20 or 24 ounce GO-CUp underneath it, unless you put some 1\" square shims underneath, or just tilt this worthless piece of garbage backward so you can put something bigger than a standard 6 oz coffee cup underneath.  In this day and age when most people actually go to a place to work, they might just wanna bring their coffee with them.  Notwithstanding the mess, the lukewarm tempertature but now I can\'t even get a half-baked cup of Joe to accompany me on my 1.5 hour commute to work without re-engineering the whole kitchen, well, again, you all need to get better user acceptance testing and pay attention to the feedback.  Because you missed the boat, big-time...I dare the engineers to fill a 24 ounce go-cup without modifying the design as it is, or tilting the machine.  Maybe I missed something but I am standing by my observation that this THING needs to be like 2 + inches taller between bottom of cup and the dispenser area so maybe we can all enjoy a cup of coffee that might, and might not, be somewhat palatable and above freezing temperature.  I would not recommend this to anyone.'),
(3647, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-20', 'Looks great on the kitchen counter Looks great. Sounds solid. Only downside is that when I am toasting one piece of bread it toasts one side a bit darker than the other. Otherwise, I like the light, crispy toasted surface it generates.'),
(3648, 6, 1, 1, '2016-10-02', 'In my 78 years this is the poorest excuse for ... In my 78 years this is the poorest excuse for a toaster ever.  Slots aren\'t wide enough for most regular bread slices.  It toasts very uneven and doesn\'t toast the same color on both sides of the bread.'),
(3649, 12, 1, 4, '2014-06-06', 'Good. Great product, but be aware that this is a very small toaster oven. I would have bought the 4 slice had I known it existed.'),
(3650, 9, 1, 3, '2016-12-10', 'great coffee temperature The best part of this coffee maker is the temperature of the coffee when dispensed_perfect level of heat. We used a regular cuisinart machine before and the coffee was never hot enough_.had to microwave each cup. I could not give a 5 star because several times, the coffee is all over the counter/floor in the morning.  I clean it properly using the designated lever to \"stop the leak\".  I am not putting more than one tablespoon of grounds per cup, but they still float up and get into the carafe area of the machine.  I\'ll try less grounds and maybe concede to making 2 pot-fulls each morning rather than the normal 10 cups.  All said, it is a wonderful machine, but needs careful use.'),
(3651, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-21', 'Five Stars Son at college in love with this.'),
(3652, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-01', 'So far so good. We bought this to replace a very expensive Cusinart toaster oven which had stopped being safe in one year.  This one is truly just as fine.  I would def recommend it.'),
(3653, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Makes good coffee! Bought this keuirg to take with me to college! I love it!!! The coffee is so good and I like that I can choose what cup size I want. The only bad thing is that I have no idea how I am going to take it with me since I am flying to college. I would totally recommend this keurig to everyone it\'s seriously a must have in everyone\'s kitchen.'),
(3654, 5, 1, 1, '2014-05-21', 'Arrived broken; didn\'t work This coffee maker arrived broken and didn\'t work. It felt cheesy and I was not pleased. I purchased the Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker instead and am so glad! I highly recommend it!'),
(3655, 8, 1, 3, '2016-07-16', 'Three Stars It\'s OK'),
(3656, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'heats up FAST Works as expected. It heats up FAST, which was a big change from the now-defunct former toaster oven that burnt out, which precipitated the need for this unit. This is not a problem. It just required getting used to how fast this thing heats up and toasts. We also use it to heat up things like fish sticks, chicken tenders/nuggets, etc. Our kids (ages 9 & 11) use this independently to melt cheese on top of their sandwiches. Their only challenge is that the knob to set the timer was a bit hard for them to turn when we first got it--which i think is a combination of the size of the dial and the comparative torque required by smaller hands to turn it. They\'ve since gotten used to it and have no issues turning the dials.'),
(3657, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-13', 'Just as Expected The toaster is great. I am very satisfied with my purchase and would recommend it to all my friends. It\'s easy to use.'),
(3658, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-09', 'Complex Directions and performance a bit complex but works perfectly.'),
(3659, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-19', 'Five Stars So far so good.'),
(3660, 5, 1, 4, '2015-01-25', 'For 50 bucks I\'d like to see these China made appliances go for at ... Worked O.K. for 8 months now no more dripping from this coffeemaker. Notified Hamilton Beach customer support via email so I\'ll see how that goes. For 50 bucks I\'d like to see these China made appliances go for at least the warranty period. Let you know how customer service works out. Although the coffeemaker did not last I have changed my rating from 2 to 4 stars due to Customer Service. Even though the product may have been inferior I found that Customer Service was very timely and responsive. Most anything you buy these days is going to be an inferior Chinese product, especially small appliances. Customer service of these companies are the only thing that make these products worth buying. Thanks Hamilton Beach.'),
(3661, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Surprisingly better than the first one I never thought it would happen. My first Keurig was amazing; had it for 3 years.  I was hurt when it stopped working.  Once I realized it was not coming back, I bought this one and it is even better. I love the option of making a full pot of copy. Very convenient.  Great value!'),
(3662, 9, 1, 3, '2017-01-09', 'Like the look of the machine Like the look of the machine, however, coffee does not stay hot for very long.'),
(3663, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-16', 'Five Stars This works very well 5 star deserving.'),
(3664, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Makes fantastic coffee, and uses K-cups or bulk ground coffee. Much easier to use ground coffee in this machine than using the adapter on a Keurig. Love this machine!'),
(3665, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-07', 'Cooks everything you would need as a regular oven. ... Cooks everything you would need as a regular oven. Heats up extremely fast and cooks just as well as a top of the line oven. I don\'t know why you would buy a full oven anymore'),
(3666, 7, 3, 5, '2016-02-22', 'Works as advertised. Follow instructions. You should have no problems. Price is right, especially if it is on sale'),
(3667, 1, 1, 5, '2016-07-06', 'Great coffee maker, love it! Great! Makes the coffee super quick and it tastes great. I received 4 sample k-cups, descaling solution and 2 water filters. I bought this to use in my dorm. It doesn\'t take up too much counter space and it\'s a beautiful color.'),
(3668, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Five Stars I returned the item as my original oven was still working'),
(3669, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-21', 'Really happy with this oven! I love this oven. I had a Black & Decker before this buy and I loved it. When I needed to replace it I wanted another Black & Decker.I didn\'t replace the first oven because it broke, but because after many years of cleaning the dials and knobs I had washed the numbers and other instructions off. I was the only one that remembered how everything worked. That is one reason I picked this oven because of the button controls. The first oven still works and I use it at times. This oven does get really warm when in use but I have never found it to be a problem. Everything I have cooked in this oven has been cooked exactly as needed. You do need to read the instructions before using. Easy to operate once you have read the instructions.'),
(3670, 8, 1, 4, '2016-10-12', 'It\'s OK Does what it supposed to do. Works good.'),
(3671, 3, 1, 4, '2016-06-19', 'Four Stars The print on the controls is very small.'),
(3672, 10, 1, 4, '2015-10-15', 'I\'m on my second one. Great if the motor holds up. I bought my first one way back in 2011. I was into smoothies and shakes then and wanted something portable that didn\'t take up a lot of space. I didn\'t need anything with a lot of different modes, just a simple blender and that is exactly what this is. I used it quite regularly for almost two years. Then it died with no warning. I turned it on one day and it did nothing at all. I checked a few things but it was clear. My blender bit the dust. I forgot about it for a while then decided i really missed it. I looked around at other brands but this one did everything I wanted and held up fairly well for being inexpensive and used so much so I purchased a second one. That one has been going strong for about eight months. I don\'t know how long it has left in it but even if I have to buy one every couple of years, it\'s not a bad deal. I could get a much more expensive blender that would probably last for ages but I don\'t need that for smoothies and shakes. I like that I can take the cup with me and not have to mess up two cups and it washes up fine. I always wash the cup by hand and dry it then put it right back on the blender for my next use. I wish it had just a bit more capacity though. 20 ounces would be great. But this one gives me enough especially if I am drinking a thick smoothie that is dense and filling. This blender isn\'t great at crushing ice or very hard things but is perfect for fruits, veggies, protein powders, and other  softer or powdered things. I liked it enough that I bought two of them and I am hoping that the one I have now will hold up longer than the first one. I would say, for the price, you really can\'t go wrong unless, of course, the motor poops out really quickly like some of the reviewers here are saying. So far, I haven\'t had that issue although I admit that the motor does seem to just die when it feels like it. Luckily I got enough time out of my first one to make it worth buying a second one.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(3673, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-02', 'Rating of purchase I actually meant to hit the 5 star button. It is a great coffe maker! Best one I have had.'),
(3674, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-23', 'This toaster oven works great This toaster oven works great. Purchased this for my brother and he loves it. No taller than a toaster and fits great on a small kitchen counter. It does not take up much space.'),
(3675, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-02', 'Just coffee, no bells and whistles....which is what I wanted. Solid, simple, does not take up too much space on my counter. I did a review search before i picked this model, everybody else seemed to like it too. No bells and whistles but i think that just means there are less things to go wrong with it. :)'),
(3676, 4, 1, 5, '2015-11-17', 'Great Toaster Oven GREAT toaster oven. Toasts bagels perfectly'),
(3677, 6, 1, 5, '2016-10-25', 'Excellent toaster Very pleased with our toaster. Works great.'),
(3678, 11, 1, 5, '2016-03-14', 'Five Stars Perfect small size'),
(3679, 4, 1, 1, '2015-05-13', 'Even with light use, doesn\'t last long I have this toaster oven and the oven stopped working.  I called Cuisinart and was told that the three year warranty doesn\'t cover postage and that I\'d have to send them the oven before they\'d send me a new one.  It is quite heavy and the postage would be nearly the cost of a new one.  So if I have to pay for a new one, it won\'t be a Cuisinart.  Reading the Q&A here, apparently many others have had difficulty with this product.'),
(3680, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'Five Stars I am happy with the product.'),
(3681, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-06', 'Five Stars Love this item.'),
(3682, 9, 1, 5, '2015-06-13', 'Best coffee maker! This is my all time favorite coffee pot! This is our second Cuisinart coffee on demand coffee maker, we simply wore the other one out.  We are avid coffee drinkers and this is the perfect pot for our household.  It is a great coffee maker.  After the coffee is made, you simply place your cup on the tray and press down the lever.  There is even a light that comes on so you can see inside your coffee cup, to make sure it is full.  The coffee is great tasting and it keeps it at a hot temperature until we have finished every drop.  It is easy to clean and fill with water.  Couldn\'t be simpler.  No messing with a heavy glass pot, or worrying about it breaking.  There is a empty and full gauge on the front of the machine to let you know how much coffee is left in the pot.  I would highly recommend this coffee maker.  It is a little more expensive than other pots, but worth every penny.  Thank you.'),
(3683, 6, 1, 5, '2014-06-03', 'does the job looks sleek and stylish. has a crumb tray hidden around the back. i love having all the options....especially the bagel option.'),
(3684, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-07', 'Five Stars Very Reliable'),
(3685, 3, 1, 4, '2016-01-13', 'Heats up super fast. Easy to use Heats up super fast. Easy to use, easy to clean. Big enough to be useful, but small enough to fit in our smallish kitchen. Fits my 8.5 x 11 casserole w/handles no problem. Can\'t yet say how long it lasts as I\'ve only had it a few weeks. I really want to give it five stars, but the power cord is super short. If you have long hair, your hair is longer than the cord. I can\'t plug it into the same outlet I used for our old toaster oven. Still, very happy with it.'),
(3686, 8, 1, 2, '2015-12-31', 'Love the size and look of this appliance but it ... I want to give this 5 stars but I can\'t because this coffee maker leaked about a cup of water all over my counter. Love the size and look of this appliance but it must be defected or something. Second time I used it i put a hand towel underneath and it was soaked through.'),
(3687, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-20', 'Three Stars Only made for single people, get a bigger one if this is for a family'),
(3688, 6, 1, 2, '2016-02-08', 'Oh where oh where is there a well-made toaster that works for years and doesn\'t cost a fortune? I now join the throngs of folks who bemoan the fact that apparently it is impossible for companies these days to manufacture a toaster that actually toasts ... and lasts. I bought this almost 2 1/2 years ago and wasn\'t thrilled with it from the start.  It toasted unevenly.  Toasting was a two-step process if my bread was taken from the refrigerator.  First you had to \"defrost\" it.  Then onward with toasting it.  We still had to put it at the highest setting to get anything resembling toast.  But we put up with it.  Yesterday it stopped working altogether. The search resumes. I am not optimistic and I refuse to spend hundreds of dollars on a toaster. How come my mother had the same simple toaster for probably 40 years and it always did its job?'),
(3689, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-02', 'Awesome Buy! WHy did I not get this sooner? Time saver, no mess, easy to use, no more bitter or watery coffee! Thanks Keurig for the free pods to get me started!'),
(3690, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-15', 'Like this better than my Kuerig which failed after 2 ... Like this better than my Kuerig which failed after 2 years and 4 months. Hopefully it last a lot longer.'),
(3691, 7, 3, 3, '2015-12-01', 'It is most convenient to have three different types of brew in one and I use all of them, sometimes in one single morning. I have pods by Wolfgang, Sumatra in regular drip and a variety of K-cups. I only wish that this machine wasn\'t made of all plastic parts. It feels flimsy and not as sturdy as my other machines. My kitchen counter is definitely neater and cleaner.'),
(3692, 12, 1, 3, '2015-11-21', 'NO TIMER. Look and works as described however I wish if it has a timer. If you turn it on and forget it will burn whatever in it and that is dangerous.  A timer should be a must.'),
(3693, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-04', 'Love it! I LOVE the detachable water holder.  I used to always make a mess and spill water when trying to fill the water for my coffee.  Not anymore, the water tank detaches easily and seats easily, perfect!  Definitely recommend.  Coffee is brewed well, stays hot, easy to use.'),
(3694, 6, 1, 4, '2015-05-18', 'Four Stars It Toast.'),
(3695, 2, 1, 4, '2015-06-02', 'Four Stars Seems to work fine, but controls a little confusing, or are we just getting too old.'),
(3696, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Five Stars MAKES GREAT COFFEE.....'),
(3697, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-12', 'Five Stars The color is amazing...works great!'),
(3698, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-12', 'Nice coffe maker Works great easy to use'),
(3699, 12, 1, 5, '2014-07-12', 'Five Stars A+++++'),
(3700, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-07', 'Great coffee well worth the money. I bought the cheap-o from walley world and damn thing warmed up and that was all - never brewed. Talking Black & Decker. This maker I would recommend to everyone.'),
(3701, 9, 1, 3, '2016-02-06', 'I\'d say it is mediocre at best. We had an under the counter unit for ... We received the Cuisinart coffee maker a few days ago.  So far, I\'d say it is mediocre at best.  We had an under the counter unit for a long time and really liked it, but they don\'t seem to make many of those anymore.  I wanted a unit that had a reservoir to fill and not have to fill the pot - then fill the reservoir.  It\'s just more efficient to have to only fill something once, and not twice.  That\'s one reason we got this one. The power cord on this unit is VERY short - like maybe 6-8 inches.  We pulled some more of it out of the base so we could at least plug it in.  The manual says it\'s short so you don\'t trip on it - but at least give a foot or two.  No kidding the cord is less than a foot.  So - if you put it under a cabinet, you may need to unplug it each day so you can open the top and put the coffee in.  You can\'t put a tall mug under the dispenser - so if you have a travel mug you use you\'ll have to fill a regular mug and then pour it into the travel mug (not very efficient).  The turn knob feels very cheap. The unit does seem to make coffee okay and it does have the program feature, etc.  But, if I had to do it over I\'d get something else.....'),
(3702, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-14', 'Four Stars We like it! Works great for us'),
(3703, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-30', 'Great coffee pot Looked at this particular model because it did not have a glass carafe, which my wife seems to break often. We love it, very easy to use and clean.'),
(3704, 10, 1, 5, '2016-10-17', 'Awesome Great blender and works very well for making smoothies.'),
(3705, 9, 1, 1, '2015-12-26', 'Makes a nice cup of coffee when working properly Makes a nice cup of coffee when working properly.  I experienced a similar defect as in other reviews ... after 3 weeks the dispenser continued to pour coffee after release. Ends up with coffee all over counter/floor.'),
(3706, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-14', 'Nice little oven Nice little oven.  Works just fine and glass window did not break like other reviews state.  Thank You'),
(3707, 5, 1, 1, '2017-01-08', 'Poor quality, like others have said Bought this as a gift for my parents that live in a different state. They got home, opened the box, and the faceplate was not attached to the unit. Should have read the reviews more carefully and gone with something else. Avoid this product!.'),
(3708, 8, 1, 5, '2015-10-31', 'Five Stars very good'),
(3709, 1, 1, 1, '2016-07-20', 'DRM Scanner ... Terrible Product. AVOID!!! Green Mountain coffee decided to put DRM scanner in this coffee maker - therefore forcing one to use only new generation, brand name only Keurig K cups with a special code. In the meantime, even official \"Keurig\" K-cups from prior generation will not work. There is a workaround - search online for instructions, but involves taping over the sensor with one of the barcodes. Overall, shameful behavior on part of the company. From the beginning, the coffee tasted terrible with plastic taste - there are once again workarounds, but why bother? BREW REAL COFFEE - avoid this wasteful, overpriced junk.'),
(3710, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-03', 'Five Stars Get here on time great item.'),
(3711, 6, 1, 2, '2015-11-20', 'Two Stars Toasting is very uneven. When the bottom half of the toast is OK, the top half is burned.'),
(3712, 8, 1, 1, '2016-04-23', 'This coffee pot is not even worth one star I ... This coffee pot is not even worth one star  I used it for 3 1/2 months every day normal wear  and It stopped making coffee .  overflowing cup and spilling all over ..  Really lousy purchase.'),
(3713, 4, 1, 2, '2016-10-29', 'seller was fantastic to big and will not cook even.  seller was fantastic.'),
(3714, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-17', 'Complete waste of Blender completely stopped working after one week of use... Complete waste of money'),
(3715, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-25', 'Five Stars Awesome toaster. I\'ve had a few of these. They look great and work very well.'),
(3716, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-25', 'Great Find! Much better than other personal blenders I just used this blender for the first time and I love it! After reading some reviews I decided to pulse the unit on and off to bled the shake rather than just holding it. By doing this I did not get any burning smell from the unit. This blender is absolutely worth the money, I had previously purchased a farberware personal blender set and they don\'t even compare. The farberware was much louder and could not crush ice while the Hamilton beach could crush ice and was MUCH quieter, and I mean like half of the noise level compared to the other unit. Absolutely an A with this purchase!!'),
(3717, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-16', 'Use my personal blender every single day and I love it. Blends very well Use my personal blender every single day and I love it. Blends very well, without having to clean up the bulky blender. I blend frozen fruit and ice together and it always turns out smooth. Great product.'),
(3718, 12, 1, 4, '2015-02-06', 'Very pleased. Very nice small toaster oven/toaster.  Both functions work quite well.  Very pleased.'),
(3719, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-06', 'Excellent toast! Replaces our S.S. Classic (4-slice retro style) Cuisinart after 10 years . . . Half the S.S. price and still with features such as \"bagel\" setting.  A new CLASSIC in white!  Excellent toast!'),
(3720, 5, 1, 1, '2016-03-11', 'Don\'t buy it. Received it 1/16/16.  Dead on 3/11/16.'),
(3721, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-16', 'Really great machine Better than expected.  Especially like the light which shines into cup when you pour - you can see in a black mug when to stop pouring.  Detachable reservoir you can fill at the sink is great too.'),
(3722, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-03', 'Makes good coffee, but you cannot use the K-cups that worked on older model machines. I found that this machine made a good cup of coffee and was easy to use with the capability to control the coffee strength. I found several good features, but several that I did not like and that these resulted in lowering my rating for the machine. Pros   Ability to control the strength of the coffee and to make cups of 4,6,8 or 10 ounces.  The machine will also brew a 40-ounce pot of coffee, but you need a special carafe that is NOT supplied.  According to the instruction the machine will also make hot chocolate, but I have not tied this.  The machine comes with a charcoal filter to remove water impurities, thereby eliminating a source of variability and poor coffee. Cons   You need special K-cups that are made for especially this machine.  According to Keurig there are other brands of coffee that make compatible cups, but not all cups will work, including those made for earlier model Keurig machines.  (I understand that there are workarounds to defeat this feature of the machine, but I have not yet tried any.  Also, see the comments section for a link to what is purported to be a refillable cup that will work with this model.  However, I have not tried this refillable cup so I cannot vouch for its operation with this model Keurig.)  While the machine makes 4,6,8 or 10 ounce cups of coffee, it is not setup for 12 ounces, which is what I usually brew.  The machine does not come with the carafe that you need for a 40-Oz pot and other carafes will not work even if they physically fit into the machine because the carafe must engage a special interlock mechanism.  While the manufacturer is well within its right to make such a design, I found it to be an obnoxious feature of the machine.  Likewise, for the incompatibility of the k-cups made for earlier models.  The k-cups are not refillable and I understand are not biodegradable, so being plastic will reside in your landfill for an unacceptably long time.  (See the comments section for a third party refillable cup that is purported to work with this model.) The fact that the manufacturer has chosen to prevent the use of older K-cups, refillable K-cups and other manufacturers carafes has led me to down-rate this machine to four-stars.  Had it been otherwise I would have rated it higher.'),
(3723, 4, 1, 3, '2015-01-11', 'Three Stars item was returned'),
(3724, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-03', 'I wouldn\'t recommend this. It couldn\'t even cut up a banana I wouldn\'t recommend this. It couldn\'t even cut up a banana! I used it once and was very disappointed.'),
(3725, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-17', 'My goal is to create a life I don\'t need a vacation from. My husband purchased the K250 for my birthday  and I love it! I have it on a small  cart in our bedroom  and can brew a cup of coffee  first thing  in the morning  while getting ready for work. Makes a cup fast when I am in a hurry! Thanks Keurig  for the free pods for this review.'),
(3726, 2, 1, 4, '2016-07-19', 'Four Stars Quick and easy to clean.'),
(3727, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-15', 'this is good Its a big toaster and it can toast a lot of pieces of bread at the same time, this is good'),
(3728, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-16', 'Simple and Convenient It\'s extremely easy to use and has all of the features that my wife and I need! It can brew 9 different sizes with the capabilities of using the Carafe sizes if we were wanting larger \'pots.\' For the price, you simply can\'t beat the convenience and the simplicity of this Keurig. I\'m sure it will have a permanent location on our kitchen counter top!'),
(3729, 11, 1, 5, '2014-01-17', 'Great toaster oven This is a terrific toaster oven at a very reasonable price.  I\'ve had B&D toaster ovens before and they don\'t disappoint.'),
(3730, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-14', 'great toaster oven Best toaster we\'ve had.  Truly I don\'t expect it to last ... all toasters seem to take longer and longer to toast over time, until one day it\'s unbearable and you get a new one.  But until the end comes, this is the perfect size for our needs, fast toasting time, and features that I will never again live without (slide out crumb tray is a MUST).'),
(3731, 12, 1, 5, '2016-03-08', 'Perfect gift. Bought as a gift for my mom. I thought it might be a silly gimick but my mom likes it alot. It\'s also very narrow which she likes so it doesn\'t stick out a bunch onto the counter.'),
(3732, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'Excellent Purchase This blender is perfect for what I needed! It is easy to use and blends very well for the price.'),
(3733, 6, 1, 3, '2016-01-08', 'Just okay, but not for homemade breads just okay. I bake my own sourdough bread. For regular white store bought bread this toaster is fine. For homemade sourdough bread it takes two cycles to brown the bread. Same with thicker breads like English muffins. I do like the feature where you can lift the bread out of the slot. That works well. Overall the toaster is reliable and works, just not for thicker breads. It is sort of annoying.'),
(3734, 4, 1, 3, '2016-07-11', 'Cuisinart TOB-40 - can\'t slide the toast out??? I like the clean lines of this product.  Fits into the stainless steel theme of my kitchen just fine.  Seems to work OK so far (one week).  But the one thing that immediately stood out is that I couldn\'t just slide the hot toast off the rack onto my plate.  The rack frame front bar forms a front barrier, requiring me to reach into the oven to grab my (hot OUCH!) toast, or use a fork to stab it to get it out.  This just is NOT right.  Soooo...  I looked at the manual, and, sure enough, the manual shows the front-to-rear rack bars spot welded on TOP of the rack frame front bar, NOT on the bottom.  So IF the frame was built per the manual, no problem to slide the toast out.  If you flip the rack over - wrong elevation.  Go figure.  So I\'m guessing Cuisinart\'s Chinese manufacturing buddies took liberties with the design, probably to make manufacturing easier somehow, and screwed-up the functionality of this product.  Other than that, OK so far.'),
(3735, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Couldn\'t be happier I have never been disappointed with any of my Amazon purchases. This is an excellent toaster oven.'),
(3736, 7, 3, 5, '2015-07-15', 'This has been great coffee maker! My coffee cups are in between the 2 heights so the coffee splashes onto the counter a little bit. ..that only criticism.'),
(3737, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Five Stars LOVE IT.'),
(3738, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'Perfect size! I love this so much that I had my sister and brother each buy one. It is the perfect size for 1-2 people and does not take up much space on the counter. Also, for those of us who are bad at following directions (me!),  the blender locks right into place with pictures that show a locked and unlocked symbol. There is only 1 button which makes it very easy to use. Love it!'),
(3739, 7, 3, 2, '2015-01-13', 'Water temperature only reached the 170\'s so I returned it. Flexibility to use K-cups or ground coffee is great but I want the brewing temperature to be at least 190.'),
(3740, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Great coffee maker I bought this one to replace the same model that I bought 8 years ago. After 8 years of 3 pots a day, It finally gave up. I love this coffee maker.'),
(3741, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-03', 'Five Stars works great.'),
(3742, 3, 1, 3, '2016-01-23', 'It\'s OK... This oven is already in storage (I\'ll keep it as a spare).  It is big and bulky in addition to the digital readout being hard to see without a back light. Check out the refurbished Cuisinart for $52.  It\'s wonderful!'),
(3743, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-03', 'oven toaster A small chicken can fit inside and this oven toaster works greater than I originally have imagined.'),
(3744, 5, 1, 4, '2014-09-17', 'Not a bad deal for the price I love the pull out water dispenser.  I have never been a fan of the cupcake style coffee basket.  I think the #4 filter size basket makes a better cup of coffee.  And, if you pour right after the brewing is finished, the coffee is not quite hot enough for my taste.  I turn the coffee maker on about a half hour before I need to start drinking my first cup, and make sure the setting for the hot plate is set to \"high\" and by then, it is fine.  Not a bad deal for the price.'),
(3745, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Great cup of coffee, every time! This is my honest review on this coffee maker, I love coffee and need it every day, we finally bit the bullet and bought this Keurig after our old coffee maker started making coffee taste bitter. It was also on sale at Target. What an amazing purchase! My kids love they can make a cup of hot cocoa instantly, and my husband has stopped buying his morning cup of coffee out, so its been saving us a little money along the way. Since we got it on sale we also bought the reusable Keurig k cup so we can also continue to use our favorite coffee if the mood strikes. All in all this was a great purchase and we are very happy. It gets used multiple times every single day! Thanks,Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3746, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Great Gift I bought this for my son\'s girlfriend and they love it!'),
(3747, 1, 1, 4, '2015-09-27', 'Works great. Had no problems with various coffee companies Works great. Had no problems with various coffee companies. May get a caddy to make it easier to add water.'),
(3748, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-17', 'Dirty & Defective product When I opened the package I noticed there were some scratches on the outside, and it looked like it had been used before. There were water spots on the cup part, as if it had been washed but not dried, and the bottom portion had some sort of film on it that I had to use soap and water to get off. No big deal, right? I figured someone returned it and now I have it. They should have cleaned it up before selling it again but whatever, they messed up. WELL, they messed up more than a little. I was sent a defective product. The blade on the cup is loose and doesn\'t respond to the portion of the cup that spins the blade from the motor. And no, you can\'t tighten it. So either they sent me a new and dirty defective blender, or they sent me a returned defective blender without cleaning or making sure it works. And it\'ll probably cost me more to return the product than to just buy a new one. This is why I stick to Ninjas. **update** I got my new Blender. It works decent for $15. I only use it at work when I have no other option. I\'ve noticed no matter how well you clean it, the cup retains the smell of whatever was in it. And if you\'re using it for protein or other shakes, you know that smell isn\'t good.'),
(3749, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-24', 'Five Stars very nice'),
(3750, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'It was well worth the upgrade! We finally made the difficult decision to upgrade from our favorite Keurig Elite brewer to the Keurig K250. I didn\'t think another brewer would be able to top the quality and flavor.  I\'m so glad we upgraded!  We love the versatility of this sleek compact brewer.  The easy to use onscreen display makes switching between cup, mug, carafe sizes, strength, etc. so easy.  Thanks, Keuring, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3751, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-25', 'Five Stars Very nice Worth the price'),
(3752, 8, 1, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(3753, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Toasts, Bakes, Broils -- compact, stainless. ... Toasts , Bakes , Broils -- compact , stainless .  Family loves it !'),
(3754, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-03', 'Very useful! Too many dials, but then again, this one can do many more things than my old toaster oven did...  LOL! The Temp Dial moves from off, to war, to 450, to broil, and then toast. The Element Dial moves from warm, broil, bake, toast. The Timer dial can either count down time, pre-set a color of toast, or stay on. Once you figure out the dials - they are quite handy and useful, making this a more versatile toaster oven than my old, reliable one that expired. Well worth the money!'),
(3755, 5, 1, 1, '2016-05-08', 'Died after two weeks This machine was good....for two weeks. The removable water reservoir is a good idea. Then it died. And would not turn on. Replugging, on/off to no avail. It lasted literally two weeks before dying. Save your money.'),
(3756, 8, 1, 3, '2016-01-18', 'Three Stars Kind of slow'),
(3757, 5, 1, 1, '2016-03-12', 'Hamilton-Beeyotch I actually like this coffeemaker a lot.  I\'m only giving it a one-star review because there are a kabillion reviews and if I were reading reviews I would look at the crappy reviews first to see what is wrong with the product.  I don\'t need more \"Great product!\" reviews. So here is what is wrong with the coffeemaker, like everybody else says (and I didn\'t read) the front face-plate practically jumps off as soon as you unpack it, along with a shower of crumbly plastic bits.  That said, a genius invented this machine, it has a removable water reservoir that and an front-load basket.  As if it were designed for humans.  My friend has a CuisineArt and you have to pour the water in this tiny slot at the top of the coffeemaker.  You have to pour slowly in order not to spill so it\'s like you turn into Rip Van Winkle before you get your Joe, your baby child becomes a grandfather as you are pouring this tiny stream of water into a tiny hole.  Not to mention I\'m groggy in the morning. I thought about getting the Mokkamaster, it looks great, but those Dutch Coffee-overlords won\'t put a simple timer on their machine for fear of ruining the purity of their product.  Maybe they have laws against it, you get 10 years of paternity leave but you have to wait for the coffee to brew in the morning.  I am just non-functional then, if a robber came I would just ask him to take my goods quietly. So the only problem I had  with the Hamilton Beach was with the front bezel.  And to tell the truth the front-plate is no prize.  it\'s brushed plastic and looks \"el cheapo\".  I did not want to glue it back in.  So instead I took epoxy putty and filled in the hollows.  Stuck a couple of metal decorations on it, and now I have a nice more steampunk-looking coffeemaker! So dear Hamilton Beach company I am sorry about slandering your brand name and giving you bad rating but I am actually trying to encourage people to buy your machine, mod it out, and make America whole/great again.'),
(3758, 8, 1, 3, '2014-06-11', 'Lesser quality I bought a 5 cup Black and Decker coffee maker almost identical to this 5 years ago until it died. Now, this newer model does not turn off automatically after a few hours and the carafe spout is small so if you pour coffee a bit quicker, it spills all over the counter. I compared the earlier version carafe and definitely the spout design is different. Why change the design when it ain\'t broke?'),
(3759, 12, 1, 3, '2015-12-17', 'Seller was prompt Arrived on time and was nicely packed.  Looks well in kitchen.  Does have a problem toasting.  Only has one coil bar and toast only in the middle of the bread/muffin/bagel.  Toaster oven burns things easily.  Would not buy another one till they improve how it works.'),
(3760, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-05', 'Great Toaster Oven for the Price The Black and Decker toaster is just as expected. It works well and is spacious enough to fit 4 small pieces of bread or four English muffin sized bagels. The timing, function and temperature dials give the product a lot of versatility. My only complaint is that the the cooking tray and rack do not come out at all when the oven door is open. Otherwise this is a very nice quality product for the price.'),
(3761, 3, 1, 3, '2016-09-14', 'Good value I like this oven a lot except one thing--if you\'re not too careful when opening the door, you could bang the handle on your countertop and scratch it. My old oven had a \"latch\" at the door that connects to the tray that prevents this from happening, giving it a certain resistance. Overall, good quality for the price.'),
(3762, 11, 1, 4, '2014-11-16', 'Delivery in 2 Days to front door, cheaper than actually Driving to a Store..so worth it. As advertised, great price and as always BLACK & DECKER quality.  Having this delivered to my mother(after a conversation on the phone about a broken Toaster and need to replace)and her front door within 48 Hours from purchase was EXACTLY why Amazon rocks!  Delivery, purchase and insured cheaper than a trip to Home Depot.'),
(3763, 6, 1, 5, '2017-01-27', 'Five Stars works great.'),
(3764, 5, 1, 2, '2016-02-10', 'Good Coffee but Questionable Durability Pros - easily programmed, multiple temperature settings for hotplate, easy to fill, makes good coffee once you get the grind correct Cons - hotplate began to rust after less than a year, warranty is essentially useless We liked this coffee maker until the hotplate began rusting after less than a year. In all my years of owning coffee makers, some of which lasted for twenty years, I have never had this happen. Hamilton Beach\'s warranty seems designed to minimize the return of defective products with onerous requirements and high shipping costs. I opted to spray paint the hotplate with Rust-Oleum high heat spray paint. I can do this a number of times at considerably less expense and hassle than trying to obtain a replacement under the Hamilton Beach warranty. After two months, the burner hotplate still looks good, but I have no idea how long this fix will last. It\'s possible we just got a defective product. Nonetheless, I doubt I\'ll purchase another Hamilton Beach when this coffee maker needs to be replaced.'),
(3765, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-11', 'B&D Toaster Very nice quality and price'),
(3766, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-09', 'Five Stars exactly what I wanted'),
(3767, 2, 1, 1, '2015-11-10', 'Buy this if you can\'t afford anything better but don\'t expect much Have had this toaster oven for a few years. Bought it because it is about the cheapest thing on the market. It has never toasted thoroughly or evenly and the oven temperature isn\'t even close to what the setting indicates. I would never attempt to bake anything in it. Because I have 4 middle to high school age kids banging on it, I don\'t want to buy a new oven when it still works (or at least works as well as it ever has). The kids have tried using this to warm microwave pizzas and stuff like that, but it\'s very inconsistent in how hot it gets. Especially if someone else already used it and it\'s still slightly warm. This is not a great appliance. I would happily replace if it fit into our budget and could see from the first time I used it that we got exactly what we paid for. Really, this is no bargain.'),
(3768, 5, 1, 3, '2015-12-05', 'Cover plate clip broke but still makes good coffee I have used the coffee pot for less than a month and it does make great coffee and the coffee is always hot.  The disappointment is that the small cover plate in the front broke.  It is held on by several small plastic clips. All I did was wipe the front of the coffee maker and the clip broke.  Now if you move the cover plate or touch to hard it falls off. I could send it back, but I would have to pay shipping for sending it to them and for the product to be shipped back to me.'),
(3769, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-21', 'Five Stars Love this thing.'),
(3770, 10, 1, 2, '2015-11-27', 'Two Stars What a cheap little junker.'),
(3771, 6, 1, 4, '2016-08-06', 'Consistent toasting, but hard to clean. We bought this toaster to make mornings go smoother for our family of five, since making toast for everyone can be time consuming. I love all the settings on this toaster, and I have used all of them. This toasts evenly and consistently on both sides. The down side, however, is its very hard to clean it out. There are crumb trays that slide out, but crumbs and other debris get stuck in other areas and you have to shake the toaster upside down to get everything out. It proved durable for many years, until one of my kids stick a twist tie in the toaster and turned it on, shorting out the elements in one side of the toaster so it no longer works. We still use the other side everyday, but I will be in the market again soon because I am missing having all 4 slots available for toasting.'),
(3772, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-27', 'Good value if you don\'t use a lot of frozen stuff Stars here are given primarily based on value; motor isn\'t particularly strong. This is not the blender for you if you plan on putting large amounts of frozen stuff in it on a regular basis. For protein powder + liquid + a few frozen berries, it works fine. I use it pretty sporadically.'),
(3773, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-21', 'Five Stars the best.'),
(3774, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-04', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker for one cup or twelve programs easy.'),
(3775, 9, 1, 1, '2015-06-01', 'Nice but overpriced and unreliable I like the coffee maker, but, after just 5 months, the hour and minute set buttons stopped working. The limited warranty requires you to pay $10 for a new coffee maker to be shipped and then pay to ship the old one back. I expect better from an $80 coffee maker.'),
(3776, 12, 1, 4, '2016-10-01', 'Love the concept and it is functional Love the concept and it is functional.  The only reason I gave it 4 stars is you cannot fit two rectangle slices(most common shape) side by side in the toaster without overlapping a bit.  That being said, they still get toasty despite the overlap.'),
(3777, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-27', 'Five Stars very nice and compact coffee maker, perfect for the light-morning coffee drinker or couple.'),
(3778, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-27', 'Five Stars Love the machine!'),
(3779, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'I love my Keurig ____ I love my Keurig. I replaced a Bun and I always said it was the best. Boy was I wrong. Thanks Keurig for the free pods and the unbiased review. I can\'t say enough about my new Keurig. ______'),
(3780, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-01', 'I love this toastation this is the third one I have I love this toastation  this is the third one I have owned'),
(3781, 5, 1, 2, '2014-07-19', 'I love this coffee pot / Update 2/21/15 - RIP I love this coffee pot!!  The water is added to a removeable tank on the back - you can take it to the sink, fill it, and just put it back.  No transferring of water (and spilling it) anymore!  Coffee grounds are exposed only with the push of a button.  Love this pot!! Purchased in July 2014 -- Died 2/21/15.  Very Disappointed.  I really liked this pot.  But after reading all the negative reviews, I think I will move on and find a better pot from a brick and mortar store.'),
(3782, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-16', 'Um..its toasted...exactly how I like it Its an excellent toaster for the price. It comes in a white color and matches my other kitchen appliances. I\'ve only used the 3 setting with and without the bagel setting for my toast. It comes out exactly how I like it, a light-medium toast on both bagels and regular sliced bread. Initially when I first used the toaster without bread there was a weird kinda of burning smell, no smoke, just a slight off putting burning smell. Maybe it was manufacturing oils or something inside. After a couple of tries, without bread inserted, the smell dissipated and I do not notice it anymore.'),
(3783, 7, 3, 3, '2016-12-01', 'The FlexBrew makes a good strong cup of coffee that tastes like it\'s fresh brewed in less than two minutes whether you use a name brand pod or use your favorite brand to fill one yourself. It is a nice little unit that might work for a longer amount of time when it is used as a personal coffee maker or used by one or two people who do not drink a lot of coffee but it is not for a family or real coffee lover. Mine was always plugged into a ground fault receptacle due to water leakage and these reviews confirm that is a common problem. I purchased two Flew Brews: the first was used by one person once a day and lasted almost five months and the second was used by two people multiple times a day and quit working after less than two months. The Hamilton Beach Brew Station makes great coffee yet I owned two each of two different styles of them and they only lasted a short time each. Though I first purchased a Keurig mini that never worked properly and failed to work at all within days, I am ordering a better model of Keurig and hoping it lasts much longer than any of the brands and models purchased in the past. Coffee pods can be expensive and their cost great increases when you must continuously purchase new coffee makers to be able to enjoy their convenience.'),
(3784, 2, 1, 2, '2015-03-30', 'It was not as good quality as the previous Black & Decker I had I guess I got what I paid for. It was not as good quality as the previous Black & Decker I had.'),
(3785, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-28', '... pizza won\'t fit but this little guy makes the perfect piece of toast Any thing bigger than a small pizza won\'t fit but this little guy makes the perfect piece of toast. I\'m talkin when you look up toast in the dictionary a picture of bread toasted in this oven would show up.'),
(3786, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-01', 'great toaster oven I\'ve been using this for about 8 months I have no complaints about it'),
(3787, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Nice toaster Great quality, great price.  Does the job and looks nice, to boot.'),
(3788, 5, 1, 2, '2015-08-05', 'Two Stars My carafe just broke only after a month of use.'),
(3789, 10, 1, 4, '2016-01-15', 'Four Stars gets the job done good'),
(3790, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-30', '4-slice toaster It toasts so well and it keeps the bread warm until its time for me to eat them'),
(3791, 3, 1, 4, '2016-08-05', 'Very good, but could use some improvements. Very nice.  Looks great and works very well.  Just two small complaints.  The door has nothing to keep it from opening more than 90 degrees.  Ours is on the counter, and it opens all the way to where the handle sits on the counter.  If you let go of the door to quickly, it drops on the counter.  Just takes once or twice to learn you don\'t want to let it go.  Second, it is difficult to read the button labels unless you have direct light on the front.'),
(3792, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'I love my machine I love my machine! I\'m a novis coffee drinker, and I use it mostly for tea. My only complaint is not with the machine, but with the favors of pods. I really wish there were more sugar free selections. Also a caraf unsweet tea from Lipton would be great!'),
(3793, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-12', 'Four Stars good price. xmas present for son'),
(3794, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-04', 'great A Christmas gift..was expressly asked for..great price'),
(3795, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-27', 'I was looking for a single brew coffee pot and this little machine is perfect. Makes the best coffee and no more waste when using a larger pot. I love it!'),
(3796, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Five Stars It\'s a great little toaster oven.'),
(3797, 12, 1, 2, '2016-03-07', 'Two Stars Toaster element stopped working in the first week.  Oven part is OK.'),
(3798, 2, 1, 3, '2016-01-27', 'Three Stars This is not covenience.'),
(3799, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Great! __ Really love this tiny machine. It\'s great for many things. I mainly use it for my protein shakes.'),
(3800, 5, 1, 1, '2014-05-27', 'I should have listened to the other reviews! The good news is - the coffee tasted good.  After a few months of one pot of coffee a day, the coffee pot started jamming and coffee would fill up the basket and overflow all over the counter and the floor.  I believe this was caused by loose coffee grounds.  No matter how careful I was, occasionally the pot jammed and I had 12 cups of coffee on the the kitchen floor.  Not a lot of fun to wake up to at 6 am.  I am very neat and even \"anal\" about kitchen appliances - this was not a result of careless cleaning.'),
(3801, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Love! I got this as a gift and absolutely love it. It looks sleek on my counter and the coffee is always hot and tastes great. I love that you can dispense just hot water for tea if you want to use a tea bag. Love this! Thank you keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(3802, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-14', 'Five Stars Works great, it was just what I ordered'),
(3803, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-25', 'Five Stars all are great'),
(3804, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-15', 'Excellent coffee maker! I read a ton of reviews on coffee makers and finally settled on this one. Love it! Best feature is the back that comes off to add water; you don\'t have to pour water into the machine. I use it on the \"bold\" setting to get a rich, delicious cup of coffee. Have had it for 6 months and zero issues.'),
(3805, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-23', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker very easy to figure out.'),
(3806, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-03', 'Great if you want a Mixer More of a mixer than a blender. Chopping does not really happen.'),
(3807, 6, 1, 2, '2014-11-24', 'We really liked it until a couple weeks after Amazons 30 day ... We really liked it until a couple weeks after Amazons 30 day return policy when it started barely toasting on one side of the bread (and it\'s definitely not on the bagel button). Now we don\'t like it because we just spent a good amount of money on a toaster that we have to pop up the bread and turn it to the other side if you want both sides toasted. Guess we got one of the unlucky ones. Definitely frustrating!'),
(3808, 8, 1, 4, '2014-09-06', 'Basic is Good_. This is very practical, basic, good working coffeemaker for those who only want a couple of cups a day. Works very well. However, it is hard to find a replacement for the carafe. I broke one and had a difficult time finding a replacement.'),
(3809, 7, 3, 1, '2015-01-14', 'Coffee, tea, ect. Does not dispense correctly. It comes out drip by drip, no steady stream, near the end of the cycle, one great strea comes out spraying everywhere. also, it will not produce a 12 ounce cup of liquid, when filling with water to the max.'),
(3810, 9, 1, 5, '2015-06-19', 'Five Stars My mom loved this as a Mother\'s Day gift.'),
(3811, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-11', 'I love this blender. I love this blender.  Use it even more than my bullet.  This i my second one in 4 years. They are durable and work well for my shakeology daily with ice and sometimes fruit.  Doesn\'t work great for blending up like a full cup of vegetables or anything like that.'),
(3812, 4, 1, 2, '2016-08-11', 'rods melted/warped - fire hazard!! Same problem as everyone else. After 4 yrs the heating rods melted/warped.'),
(3813, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-12', 'Five Stars Awesome 5-cup coffee maker! Simple to use, brews grounds well.'),
(3814, 4, 1, 1, '2015-01-08', 'This oven top element burnt out within a year i/2 ... This oven top element  burnt out within a year 1/2  M.L. Up until then I liked it!'),
(3815, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-16', '... for 3 weeks now and have read all the bad reviews. I have only had this oven for 3 weeks now and have read all the bad reviews..As far as I\'m concerned you can\'t go wrong for 30 bucks..Would I bake something in it for over 30 minutes? NO WAY..it\'s purpose is simple..to toast bread and reheat leftovers without having to turn on your oven.. By using common sense your handle won\'t melt, glass won\'t explode and grease dripping on the heating element won\'t cause it to blow or start a fire..cooking bacon,  pork chops or anything fatty is dangerous..it\'s also to small to do anything other then reheat or toast.. I love the broiler feature and now don\'t have to turn on my Viking range for simple things like melting cheese on bread..this isn\'t an oven and be careful where you place it because it does get hot..I wouldn\'t run it for more then 15 minutes max as a safety measure..'),
(3816, 1, 1, 1, '2016-06-03', 'Don\'t buy anything from this moron! This idiot shipped this coffee maker with water still in it. All circuits were toast.'),
(3817, 2, 1, 1, '2015-07-15', 'CRAP I received the item_plugged it in and the power light comes on but doesn\'t heat up. Now I have to pay the company 7.50 for shipping of a new one when it isn\'t my fault the crappy product doesn\'t work. So my 30$ toaster oven is turning into a 40$ piece of crap. I understand that things don\'t work sometimes_it happens_.but to then charge me to ship a new one? horrible.'),
(3818, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-11', 'Caution - Read Before Purchasing.  Safety Hazard!!! I\'ve always had great experiences with Cuisinart products which is what led to my purchase of a TOB-40 toaster over.  I was attracted to this model due to the great company reputation and warranty.  This unit was replaced under warranty in Oct 2014 due to a faulty heating element.  Cuisinart was great about replacing it as long as I paid shipping for the replacement unit as well as shipping back to them for my broken unit.  I still figured this was better than purchasing a completely new unit.  If you do some searches on the web, the faulty heating element seems to be a known issue.  Some people have also reported this to the Consumer Products Safety Commission as this could be a fire hazard and were hoping for a recall. My replacement unit worked great until just the other day. After using the oven to toast waffles for my kids, the toaster was turned off and out of the blue the glass completely shattered and exploded.  Thankfully, my kids were not near the unit as they could have been injured as a result of this explosion.  I\'ve included a picture of the unit post explosion for you to see.  I called customer service and spoke to a rep who basically said that since the warranty was tied to my original unit and that transferred to the replacement unit (which has now expired) there was nothing that they could do on this defective 4 month old unit.  I asked to speak to a supervisor and spoke with Shelby who gave me the same answer that there was nothing that could be done.  I could understand if my unit just stopped working after an extended period of time.  But this is a serious issue on a relatively new unit that could have resulted in serious injury. I\'m very disappointed in the customer service and policy that is in place by Cuisinart.  I would have hoped that keeping a loyal customer happy would be more important to them instead of worry about saving the money on a product that costs them less than $100 to replace.  You\'ve now lost a customer for life and I strongly urge anyone interested in purchasing their products to think twice.'),
(3819, 12, 1, 4, '2016-08-02', 'Red toaster My third red toaster by Hamilton Beach. It toasts well and I do like it, but It was missing t h e crumb tray.Rats!.'),
(3820, 6, 1, 4, '2015-09-28', 'I like the push button controls Works well. Smaller than my old toaster- more compact, freeing up counter space.  I like the push button controls.'),
(3821, 9, 1, 3, '2016-12-02', 'Good tasting coffee Good tasting coffee. The coffee gauge has never worked.  Next time I\'ll buy a coffee machine with a stainless steel coffee reservoir. Of course I\'ll have to pay more for it.'),
(3822, 10, 1, 1, '2015-04-15', 'Don\'t bother This thing is flimsy. It won\'t blend frozen fruits and can barely handle ice. I guess if you just want pulped fruit or a well blended protein shake it\'s fine. I wouldn\'t waste your money.'),
(3823, 12, 1, 4, '2015-03-23', 'This is used in an office breakroom. I haven\'t ... This is used in an office breakroom.  I haven\'t personally used it yet, but comments from co-workers have been very positive.'),
(3824, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-10', 'One Star Did not work at all. Very disappointing.'),
(3825, 6, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Good toaster for the money Good toaster for the money. I really like the bagel setting and that the lever allows you to raise up the smaller items without having to stick your fingers or knives in the toaster..'),
(3826, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Good coffee maker Like the wheels on the bottom'),
(3827, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Cuisinart coffee on demand It\'s great, no pot to worry about and it\'s easy to clean.'),
(3828, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-31', 'Great Great'),
(3829, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-09', 'I am really enjoying this coffee maker. Quick and easy to use.'),
(3830, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-04', 'Very pleased with my purchase of the Cuisinart DCC-3000 Coffee-on-Demand 12-cup ... Very pleased with my purchase of the Cuisinart DCC-3000 Coffee-on-Demand 12-cup coffee maker.  I have no negatives at all concerning this product.  I recommend it.'),
(3831, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-21', 'Hamilton Beach Coffee Maker Love it and use it daily'),
(3832, 11, 1, 4, '2016-02-16', 'Nice, Inexpensive Toaster Oven So, I\'ve had this for over 2 years but have only used it almost half a year.  In my previous kitchen was an overpriced, giant toaster oven - boy was it really nice though.  So, when I finally moved and broke this one out, I was kind of like, \"Hey little fellow....\"  While I\'m not going to be putting pizza\'s in this like the last one I used, it does the job for some of the most basic things I am cooking.  Most of the things I use it for are bread, or maybe heating up something slowly, or whatever - but nothing too complex.....yet. And it works fine.  I really have no complaints.  The dials are all twist-turn and it\'s nothing overly fancy, but it has worked well for me so far.  I\'d say this is definitely worth the price.'),
(3833, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-21', 'Toasts great, bakes great Toasts great, bakes great, reheats great and it is easy to dump out the crumb tray. What more can I ask for? Great product, highly recommended.'),
(3834, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-13', 'One Star Do not buy this product because not working properly I couldn\'t do anything with it');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(3835, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-28', 'Good Bought this for my desk at the office and it\'s great. Basic but just what I needed. Didn\'t want all the bells and whistles, just something to get me a good cup of joe'),
(3836, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-27', 'I bought this coffee maker a couple of months ago (like to wait how I really like an item before making a review...) I thought coffee didn\'t taste the same at first, but I adjusted the amount of coffee I was using and now I wouldn\'t use anything else. I make just one cup at the time on most days, but it\'s also great for making a few cups, as it brews very quickly. I like the fact that you can use your own coffee with it.'),
(3837, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'great toaster. I bake & freeze rolls & this ... great toaster. I bake & freeze rolls & this toaster has wide enough bays & I love the defrost & warming settings.'),
(3838, 6, 1, 2, '2015-02-01', 'Cuisinart should have better quality control for who ever manufactures their toasters Cuisinart should have better quality control for who ever manufactures their toasters. Tried two toasters and both toasted bread dark on one side and light on the other in their normal toast mode. Bought a Black and Decker instead.'),
(3839, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-28', 'Great for meals for one. It works well, looks sharp, and meets my needs.'),
(3840, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-15', 'Looks similar to more expensive coffee makers and I like the fact that I can change the temperature for ... It is hard to find a reliable decently priced coffee maker but this is the one. Looks similar to more expensive coffee makers and I like the fact that I can change the temperature for heating the coffee. Makes a good pot of coffee.'),
(3841, 4, 1, 1, '2015-11-24', 'I wouldn\'t recommend and/or repurchase The toaster over was damaged when I received it -- a big dent in the top to be exact, and the door is loose.  I reached out immediately with that complaint, but never heard a response. I wouldn\'t recommend and/or repurchase.'),
(3842, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-26', 'I really wasn\'t sure how this would work out. I am not wasting coffee the way I was in the past the coffee is much better. My daughter had bought the Mr.Coffee version which was junk it never worked. This beauty worked great right out of the box I do recommened running 3 or 4 cycles of just water through just to clean out anything left in the manufacturing process. It\'s a solid machine and wonderfully fast too.'),
(3843, 7, 3, 2, '2015-12-09', 'The filter supplies does not work.Using less than the maximum allowed, it overflows and starts to build up along the top of the machine (you won\'t notice unless you look) Reusable k-cup filters don\'t fit Amount of coffee dispensed is inconsistent from 1 cup to the next even when using the exact same amount of grinds. Splatters coffee while brewing.'),
(3844, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-08', 'Five Stars great for 4 cupper.'),
(3845, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-03', 'toasted bread pizzas This machine has made my toasted bread pizzas really good'),
(3846, 8, 1, 3, '2016-02-29', 'Very basic coffeemaker. This is a very simple, no bells or whistles coffeemaker. There is not even a no-drip feature if you want to pour a cup before it has finished brewing. It works fine. Maybe has less to go wrong than its more complicated rivals.'),
(3847, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-31', 'I like it. Yes, it is as described. I like it.'),
(3848, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-17', 'Love the front opening feature. Very happy with this coffeemaker. Easy to set, like the visual bright blue clock and love that the button pops open the basket from the front and we do not have to lift the top, so now it fits in the corner of my counter and does not have to be pulled out to make coffee. We did buy a universal permanent coffee filter that works perfectly. Coffee is done quickly and nice and hot.'),
(3849, 9, 1, 3, '2016-01-21', 'Good maker, but hard to clean Had I posted this review 5 months ago when I purchased it,  it would have easily been 5 stars.  Today I see I never reviewed it, so I shall now.  This unit is terribly hard to keep clean and I am in ongoing e-mail conversations with Cuisinart about this fact.  The black plastic, interior unit (the \"coffee holder\") has so many nooks and crannies, you can never get it satisfactorily clean. Based on the manual I was running the half water/half vinegar self clean cycle once a month since August.  In between self clean cycles, I would also wipe the interior with \"warm, soapy water\" (again, the manual) every so often to clean it. I thought this was satisfactory until 4 days ago.  Our morning coffees had \"floaties\".  I dumped the coffee and began to inspect the interior while over the sink.  I began to see all the areas I really could not reach.  What I could reach, I found massive coffee residue build up.  I began to tackle the interior with warm, soapy water and scrubbing the best I could, using rags, dish brushes, and even an old toothbrush.  This was producing massive black flaking.  I then let white vinegar soak in the reservoir. Rinsing, I found more and more black flaking flowing into the sink with every dump of water through the black reservoir.  Now it never stops.  I have created a monster.  Every towel I use to wipe and dry to view my progress, comes away black as soot.  My wife is now \'grossed out\' and will not drink from the DCC-3000 any longer. I never dreamed this DCC-3000 would be so difficult to keep clean, even following a good cleaning regime previously.  Why does the \'self clean\' cycle not really clean the unit?  Why am I having to roll up the sleeves and really scrub?  And with an old toothbrush?  It\'s only been 5 months of ownership.  It shouldn\'t be this difficult. Edit, January 27, 2016: Since writing this, Cuisinart has suggested that using only vinegar and water while utilizing the unit\'s self-clean cycle may not be enough to keep the DCC-3000 clean.  I am now being told that to truly clean the interior to utilize a product like CleanCaff for the coffee residue.  I wish when I had asked how best to keep clean 5 months ago, this advice had been given back then.  Instead for now, Cuisinart is going to replace this unit with another DCC-3000 for my troubles, even though nothing is technically wrong with the unit.  I thought that was a nice act.  They even waved their $10 processing fee.'),
(3850, 6, 1, 4, '2015-07-03', 'Love it For a compact toaster it looks and works great! Good price. The only complaint I have is the toast button. It is huge. Stands out very far from the front of the toaster. I have to store it at an angle in my counter garage. Strange thing to do to a compact toaster. Else.. Love it!'),
(3851, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-10', 'After only 1 month, started to brew only 1/4 cup, then the next coffee would overflow....Some days, no coffee would get brewed at all. Also, I would find coffee grains inside, despite cleaning the tip regularly as it was recommended...After speaking to Hamilton Beach (which are very rude), they did replace the coffee machine but I was responsible for shipping charges. I just got my new Flexbrew today and guess what...SAME PROBLEM!'),
(3852, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-16', 'Great toaster. Just what I needed, a compact and fast toaster.'),
(3853, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-22', 'Good, affordable coffee maker Nice coffee maker for the money. Very easy to use. Like the adjustable warming feature.'),
(3854, 1, 1, 1, '2015-09-16', 'only used it to make ONE cup of tea every ... only used it to make ONE cup of tea every morning and it quit working after 1 month.  Won\'t dispense fluid and is stuck in the preheating mode.'),
(3855, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-29', 'Our second Cuisinart toaster and we love it Our second Cuisinart toaster and we love it. Toasts BOTH sides which our old one didn\'t. Love the \"Reheat\" feature for when the toast is done before the eggs. Slightly narrower than our old one too. But why is so hard to find a white toaster?.'),
(3856, 2, 1, 4, '2016-07-12', 'Got it to toast The setting on this thing is really confusing. All the knobs and different options. It does the job now that I\'ve finally figured it out how to just TOAST.'),
(3857, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-08', 'i cant use it anymore and its ready for the garbage. it lasted a little less then the 30 ... after a very short time of using it it started burning everything i put in. the glass door got all black from the smoke. i cant use it anymore and its ready for the garbage. it lasted a little less then the 30 day warranty. but i didnt get my $$ back for it'),
(3858, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-01', 'Use this almost every day. I had an older ... Use this almost every day. I had an older model for years & it still worked after more than 20 years. Just wanted a new one as the old one was beginning to be an eyesore & wanted a more contemporary model. There are just 2 people in my household, so this works perfectly for reheated & cooking a smaller amount of food & reheating in order to keep the food crisp. Hope this model lasts as long as the old one.'),
(3859, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Looks nice and works well Looks nice and works well. I mostly just make a 4 cup pot once or twice a day and the \"1-4\" cup brew option really does make it taste better by brewing it slowly. I liked this one because the water compartment is completely separate from where you put the grounds. This prevents cross contamination and build up over time. It\'s the best drip coffee make I\'ve ever owned.'),
(3860, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Five Stars Just awsome my wife loves it'),
(3861, 5, 1, 1, '2015-12-07', 'A disappointing and potentially dangerous item I purchased this coffee maker August 2014. At first it seemed to working fairly well but over the last six months it has been taking longer and longer to brew. Over the last few days it has been taking three hours to brew four cups of coffee. We have soft water so I did not expect scaling but I investigated options in the manual. The manual gives you a vinegar treatment but does not say what it is for or when to apply it. I decided to try it today and surprisingly the coffee maker blew up after about 45 minutes. What they don\'t tell you is that acetic acid plus calcium carbonate release CO2 gas which is explosive especially when heated under pressure as instructed. The outcome was hot vinegar sprayed all over my kitchen and a totally trashed coffee maker. Fortunately nothing worse happened and I was not in the kitchen when it happened. I would not buy this unless you life lacks for excitement'),
(3862, 6, 1, 4, '2014-01-11', 'Nice Toaster Nice toaster. Browns bread, bagles, english muffins, Pop Tarts evenly. Like the reheat feature. One side a bit difficult to latch into toasting position, indicating an assembly and adjustment problem. Recommend it as a \"buy\", but check out that you can easily push down and latch the toaster levers.'),
(3863, 8, 1, 5, '2014-04-15', 'Perfect size! I bought this to replace a 4-cup Mr. Coffee for two reasons: I wanted a coffee maker slightly bigger and preferred one in black since the white gets stained and Mr. Coffee does not make a 5 cup other than in white. This little gem is perfect. It makes three mugs of coffee (the first thing I did was to measure it against the Mr. Coffee carafe and it is bigger) and has a very nice and sturdy handle. What more could anyone ask for? Am very happy with my purchase.'),
(3864, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-14', 'One Star No turn off switch'),
(3865, 4, 1, 2, '2015-11-20', 'Really expected better from something with the Cuisinart name This has been used - maybe - twice a month since I bought it Sept 2013.  It still toasts - barely - but the bake function is kaput.  set oven for 350 temp, 30 minutes later, it\'s only at 200 degrees.  Really expected better from something with the Cuisinart name, especially something sold on a military base.'),
(3866, 10, 1, 4, '2015-06-09', 'I\'ve been very happy with it over the past 3 years and would ... Purchased from another vendor in 2012 and it\'s just now starting to show signs of age. It\'s becoming difficult to lock and unlock, and the cup itself is starting (barely) to show signs of a leak. I\'ve been very happy with it over the past 3 years and would recommend it again. For the price, 3 years is a great lifetime.'),
(3867, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-20', 'Four Stars great buy if you want something small.'),
(3868, 12, 1, 1, '2014-04-24', 'Avoid Hamilton Beach/Nacco products This product broke within the 1st year, the oven just stopped working. When I contacted their customer service, they argued with me and insisted I pay $8 for shipping a warranty replacement. I would need to send in the money, then cut off the cord and email them a picture of the destroyed product. Then wait 2 weeks for a replacement. My argument back: Why pay $8 for a piece of crap? Their reply was I could get another model for the replacement instead. I looked at their other models and all have terrible reviews. (I read the 1 and 2 star reviews from Verified purchasers) Hamilton Beach is a subsidiary of NACCO Industries. They do COAL mining. That\'s right, a major pollutant industry in the USA is also making and selling crap products. No big surprise there I suppose. I will not be paying $8 or even 1 penny for another of their garbage products. Instead, I will pay for a good solid product that has great reviews. Thankfully Amazon makes this process very easy with their reviews system of Verified purchasers. (I don\'t trust Vine reviews. The idea Amazon is sending someone a free product to review and expecting them to give it a poor rating is unlikely.)'),
(3869, 12, 1, 4, '2015-10-25', 'Four Stars Doesn\'t toast all the way through'),
(3870, 2, 1, 3, '2015-05-22', 'Three Stars Not very good for toasting..it takes too long'),
(3871, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-08', 'Have Used For Months Without Problems I have been using this for months and I have no complaints.  It has not leaked despite constantly removing the water reservoir and the strength adjuster is nice.'),
(3872, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-01', 'The little blender that could. Great single blender. Makes a bit of a smell though if you use it too long. I even use it to make basil butter and I\'ve had no problems. It\'s still going as strong as the day I bought it.'),
(3873, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-06', 'Five Stars I love this coffee pot.  Second one I have owned.  Hope this one lasts longer than the original!!!'),
(3874, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-16', 'Great coffee maker! I was looking for a coffee maker with a removable water reservoir and found this one. It works very well. I especially like how easy it is to program the time and delayed brewing function. It definitely lives up to its description.'),
(3875, 4, 1, 4, '2015-08-30', 'It\'s very difficult to see the placement of the dials ... It\'s very difficult to see the placement of the dials. Plus there is no visible timer for you to know how much time is left. But it does cook quickly and evenly.'),
(3876, 2, 1, 1, '2016-09-21', 'One Star set on fire twice!.'),
(3877, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-19', 'very good toaster oven Its a very good toaster oven, its perfect for making small pizza'),
(3878, 8, 1, 4, '2016-03-12', 'It is a good coffee maker for the price It is a good coffee maker for the price.  My only complaint is that the coffee continues to drip when you remove the pot, so I have to wait for the coffee to be all made before I can pour a cup.  It\'s tough to wait five minutes at six am.'),
(3879, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-19', 'Use this more than my main oven I bought this mainly for its size.  I like the width as it can handle larger pans than others I shopped for.  Heats quickly and toast evenly.  Use this more than my main oven.'),
(3880, 12, 1, 1, '2014-12-05', 'spend the exra money and get a good Dented when it came! No pullout tray to clean it...not tray to bake on..spend the exra money and get a good one'),
(3881, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Very pleased with purchase Very good coffeemaker.  Coffee is hot.  Unit is attractive'),
(3882, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-07', 'Five Stars works great and looks great'),
(3883, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-25', 'Not Just For Coffee - TEA! I bought this on a whim...I\'m a tea drinker as of late. It\'s starting to get cold at night and I wanted something to keep my already made tea hot. I tried the little mug warmers they sell that you plug in, but they don\'t keep my drink as hot as I would like it. I love my Hot Shot water boiler but it only made the hot water, and does not keep my tea hot. I looked, and looked, and thought and brain-stormed.  Ta-da...THIS! I can run hot water through the machine, into the carafe, and have hot water all day/night until I turn it off. I can make my tea (or instant oatmeal, instant hot chocolate, 3 in 1 coffee packets, from this hot water.  OR.... I can use my own glass teapot infuser on the bottom, let the hot water pour into the infuser through the tea/tisane I have in the filter and make my tea and keep it piping hot as I drink it. (I use one like this that I bought on e-bay: )  OR... I can heat the water into the B&D carafe, pour it into a teapot to infuse, then pour it back into the B&D carafe to keep it hot (if the infuser doesn\'t fit the machine). I LOVE that the switch (on/off) is on the right side and also the water fill gauge on the right as I\'m disabled (severe RA in most joints)  and in bed a lot so this sits right on my lower nightstand (make-shift) tea bar. When I wake up in the morning I have my hot tea before getting out of bed. I can see that the coffee maker is on by the glowing red light on the switch so I can turn it off when done. I don\'t have to call out for someone to make me a hot drink (bothering them) and I feel good about being able to do this myself (feeling of accomplishment). I can also make my evening tisanes/herbals the same way without any help. I keep 3 - 24 ounce bottles of water with me so I can drink to my heart\'s content all day and evening without getting up. The teas and tisanes keep me from munching out of boredom so this in-turn is healthy for me. Some teas I add a touch of sugar (kept in a small mason jar with lid) and a Mini-Moo (half and half) for richness (especially on the masala chai) but mainly I drink them plain. No matter how I\'m drinking it, this machine keeps the tea nice and hot. I mainly use the B&D carafe for keeping hot water so in the morning I can make a miso soup, then instant oatmeal, then a small pot of tea. I use my own small teapots for keeping my made tea hot until it\'s finished...the hotplate keeps it very hot. I accidentally ordered 2 (didn\'t notice until they arrived) and after using one I decided to keep the other in case this one breaks. At twelve dollars and some change I couldn\'t go wrong with trying this to see if it would meet my needs...it does and it does it well. I am pleased. ETA: This isn\'t a coffee maker that you can pull out the carafe and the coffee will stop pouring out - it\'s a continuous drip through the filter into the carafe.  This is exactly what I wanted for making tea, I wanted the water to keep flowing into different sized teapots/mugs and not have to rely on only having to use their carafe. ETA: This is AWESOME! I had leftover tea from the night before and reheated it on the keep warm plate -- the tea got piping hot within an hour and I\'m enjoying the rest of the tea.'),
(3884, 5, 1, 1, '2015-05-11', 'Piece of junk. Suddenly stopped working after 16 months ... Piece of junk. Suddenly stopped working after 16 months. Might as well buy a cheaper coffee maker at half the price, rather than be duped into thinking you\'re getting quality at double the price. Shame on you, Hamilton Beach!'),
(3885, 4, 1, 5, '2016-10-15', 'Five Stars For this price a good quality and handling simple and now electronic screen; better for retirees.'),
(3886, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-06', 'Awesome. I don\'t know why I waited so long ... Awesome.  I don\'t know why I waited so long to get a pod system!!.'),
(3887, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-06', 'Love my toaster oven Love my toaster oven.  Does everything I need it to.  Glad I found another Black and Decker toaster oven to replace my old Black and Decker.'),
(3888, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-21', 'Great design and function Love this toaster - multi functional.  Used to have the 4 slice - they no longer make it - if they ever bring it back will buy again!'),
(3889, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-07', 'Great product! Work like a charm and is cute too!'),
(3890, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Especially like this coffeemaker because it has a detachable water reservoir Especially like this coffeemaker because it has a detachable water reservoir. Very convenient for filling with water without spilling!.'),
(3891, 11, 1, 4, '2014-02-25', 'Good basic toaster This toaster works well for all types of bread but is a slight bit small for warming other small plates. The tray is even smaller than the rack.'),
(3892, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-13', 'Good Quality Coffee Maker Very nice features. No dribbles when pouring from a full pot. Makes good tasting coffee. The removable water tank is convenient.'),
(3893, 7, 3, 5, '2014-05-30', 'Great price for online sale. Auto shutoff. Coffee ready in cup app 2 min..'),
(3894, 7, 3, 1, '2016-08-17', 'Does not even make 1/2 cup when you put in max water. I tried it for seven days, taking it back tomorrow.'),
(3895, 2, 1, 1, '2015-07-16', 'One Star Low quality product. I returned it.'),
(3896, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-18', 'Does a great job This toaster oven does a great job for me. I use this a lot more than my regular oven.'),
(3897, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-22', 'One Star Doesn\'t work at all, the blades are WAY TOO SMALL.'),
(3898, 10, 1, 3, '2016-01-05', 'Three Stars mediocre'),
(3899, 5, 1, 2, '2015-05-07', 'Leaky water reservoir Got this to replace an older Cuisinart Grind and Brew that my husband \"hulk smashed\" the lid on by accident. I bought it because I was looking for something that had a water reservoir I could see. Unfortunately this detachable reservoir leaks. The stopper should only release water when it\'s set in it\'s place and the stopper is pushed up, but this leaked brand new out of the box.'),
(3900, 5, 1, 4, '2016-09-06', 'Front face plate sprung off like most of the reviews mentioned - was aware of ... Front face plate sprung off like most of the reviews mentioned - was aware of this before buying.  A little super glue fixes this.  Made in China.'),
(3901, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-28', 'I am just so pleased with our new Hamilton Beach Single-Serve Coffee Maker!! On the weekends I make a full pot of coffee for my husband in the morning, but on work days, he always just waited until he arrived at work for his first cup of the day. Now that we have this little single serve, he can have one cup before he leaves for work and that gets his day off to a great start. I\'m not a big coffee drinker, but this is just so quick and handy, I find myself fixing a cup for me during the morning when before I wouldn\'t have bothered making a pot just for me. It\'s very fast and easy and since I don\'t like my coffee very strong, I just use a very small amount (around a teaspoon full), fill my favorite \"tea rose\" cup with water, dump in the coffee maker and in less than 3 minutes have a great cup of coffee. It\'s very easy to clean and I love not having to wash out a coffee pot. Just dump the grounds, toss the very few used grounds in the garbage, rinse the little basket and I\'m done. Couldn\'t be more pleased!!!'),
(3902, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-04', 'Five Stars excellent product more than I expected'),
(3903, 9, 1, 2, '2015-12-30', 'Stopped working correctly within a year (10 months) Was a good coffee maker, but it died within a year. After about 6 months it wouldn\'t suck all of the water through, so you would have to run it twice for one full brew. The last few months that we used it the water would only go through a cup or two a time, so we\'d have to \"brew\" up to 5-6 times for one actual brew. It got to the point that it just wasn\'t worth it anymore. Also, fyi there is a hot plate inside the machine, so even though you don\'t see it you may still end up with a burnt flavor after it\'s been on for a while.'),
(3904, 9, 1, 1, '2016-11-18', 'I like the no carafe concept I set the \"Auto brew\" function and wake to coffee all over the counter. This my second purchase of the same machine.  I bought and returned one 3 months for the same reason.  I like the no carafe concept, so thought I would try again and am now having the same problem.'),
(3905, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-16', 'Five Stars does a great job and looks great too'),
(3906, 4, 1, 5, '2016-11-30', 'Woks Well I love this Toaster Over. I use it most of the time instead of heating up the oven. It work well. The only problem have encounter is the pan that is included stains and it is impossible to remove. I put aluminum foil on the pan now.'),
(3907, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-28', 'One of the best Probably the best coffee maker with removable water tank out there. This was a replacement for an identical one, which was pushed off the counter by accident.'),
(3908, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Love this machine Love this machine!  Easy to Program, slides easy from until the cabinet. back tank just comes off, you fill it and put it back on...no dumping. It looks nice too.'),
(3909, 2, 1, 3, '2016-08-10', 'Does the job, but toasting bread needs a little research It\'s only an ok purchase because: - When toasting bread, you should keep you eye on it. The bottom side of your toast will toast quicker than the top. Also you need to figure out the balance of where you place your toast as well- that makes a big difference on what part gets toasted vs. burned. - Handle has not melted off my unit yet. This was a large concern for me when I was reading other reviews. - I put frozen mac + cheese in the toaster oven, and the paper bowl the m + c comes in gets burned, unless I cover it with foil. Even then, sometimes the paper burns because the toaster oven gets really out. So beware- this is not the fault of the toaster oven, just letting you know. Overall, this toaster oven does it\'s job. It\'s very affordable, and doesn\'t take up much counter space. Some of the fancier ones take up quite a bit of space!.'),
(3910, 9, 1, 2, '2015-11-29', 'I love the concept of on demand and the temperature the ... I love the concept of on demand and the temperature the coffee remains at, but I have been putting up with coffee grounds in my coffee as it is dispensing. The bottom of my cup has grounds which is inexcusable!! I use the gold filter or paper filters as I experimented with each and same result_ After coffee is brewed I go to clean and the inside of the lid is covered w/grounds!! Splattered all over inside! Thus is terrible. Please let me know why this is and if there is a solution to this problem. This is my 2nd Cuisinart as I thought it was maybe a lemon and did not want to deal w/returning and then warranty issues. The 2nd purchase has the same problems and I may have to junk and stay away from Cuisinart!! So sad __'),
(3911, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-15', 'Five Stars Best of the ovens'),
(3912, 5, 1, 2, '2014-05-22', 'display inoperative I ordered my model 46201 and found that nothing worked on the display except the on/off button -- it does make coffee. No time setting, no programing,no brew cycle etc. Hamilton beach say they will send a new one if i send in picture of the disabled (cord cut) pot and a copy of the online receipt. KEEP YOUR RECEIPT! In the meantime no coffeemaker unless I splice the cord back on. Another piece of Chinese crap!!'),
(3913, 6, 1, 3, '2014-07-25', 'Three Stars It is O K but will not handle longer slices of bread. Now we use it only for bagels.'),
(3914, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-07', 'Five Stars A great little toaster'),
(3915, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-30', 'Little toaster oven does a good job. It has a low profile which I like and Works so much better than my old one. Won\'t do 4 very big pieces of toast but will do 4 small or medium pieces. Wasn\'t sure if it was going to work well with only two heating elements (one top, one bottom). I\'m happy that I took a chance on it. It does a good job. Due to different sizes and moisture levels of your breads and bagels, I would stay keep an eye on toast rather than walking away until you know how your particular toaster oven works. The inside is the same size as my old toaster oven with the outside being quite a bit smaller. So, it has a much lower profile in my kitchen and leaves me with more space which is nice. So far I am very happy with it. It\'s simple and efficient and was in my price range.'),
(3916, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-30', 'Five Stars Easy to operate.'),
(3917, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-05', 'Love it as much as the same model it replaced Love it as much as the same model it replaced.  The last one was still working fine but we liked it so well we bought this as a spare.'),
(3918, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'Good coffee maker So far, pretty good. I really like the Keep Warm temperature level option. I\'m one of the few weirdos out there who does not like my coffee very hot. In fact, I like it just kind of warm, so I typically let it sit in my mug for a few minutes before I start drinking it. (My last coffee maker was a Mr Coffee with way too hot of a hot plate, and it was always burning the carafe) With this Hamilton Beach coffee maker, you can be the weirdo with the not-too-hot coffee, or you can have it stay very hot. The option is very nice. I would say, however, that my coffee isn\'t as strong as I like with this machine, even using the Bold function. I have to add 25-50% more ground coffee to get it to where I like it -- but that\'s probably just me, as I like my coffee pretty strong.'),
(3919, 12, 1, 1, '2016-08-14', 'Product is now working poor and oven heats very slow even on highest settings Purchased item on April 29th 2016 and it was delivered on May 1 2016.  Product is now working poor and oven heats very slow even on highest settings. I have had two previous purchases prior to  the April 29th purchase and was very satisfied with product and it\'s longevity. However  this one only lasting  4 months is completely unacceptable. I have to cheek with company to see how long original warranty is for . Will post a follow-up review at a later date.'),
(3920, 8, 1, 1, '2014-09-26', 'One Star Poor Quality. This item is already scratched and dented.'),
(3921, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-24', '... this coffee maker for about 3 years & absolutely love it. Haven\'t had any issues & would highly ... We\'ve had this coffee maker for about 3 years & absolutely love it. Haven\'t had any issues & would highly recommend this product!'),
(3922, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-02', 'Happy coffee drinker Love this coffeemaker.  It\'s nice and sturdy so when you push against it with your cup the machine will stay in place and not slide back. I had bought a cheaper machine before this one which kept sliding back each time I push my cup against the dispenser.'),
(3923, 4, 1, 1, '2015-07-20', 'One Star Coils split and bent.'),
(3924, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Great Instant Coffee Maker for the Price My office still has the old style brew a whole pot of coffee which is really annoying when you need coffee now and its empty.  I purchased the Keurig 2.0 for home and its so nice being able to have a cup of coffee in seconds as well as to get a variety of different types of coffee and teas so many people can enjoy.  Only thing I do not like about it is that the water tray is behind the Keurig.  This means, pulling the Keurig out and lifting up the tray from behind instead of lifting it from the side like other versions.  All in all, still a great single serve coffee maker (have not tried brewing a Carafe yet). Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3925, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Five Stars a perfect toaster.'),
(3926, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-06', 'Satsified purchase.... Exactly as I expected.  The hinged door pull out rack makes it very easy and safe to remove food from the oven.  Don\'t understand why it was removed from the newer models.  Glad I was able to get this one.  It is my second one to own.  Now I have one at Mom\'s house and one here at my home.'),
(3927, 5, 1, 4, '2015-07-24', 'Excellent with one exception This coffee maker has great features and I\'m glad I chose it. However, the carafe is poorly designed. The last ounce of coffee pours out only when the carafe is upside down over the sink.'),
(3928, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-15', 'Nice looking but a complete fail for actual usage Looks nice but that\'s the only thing going for it. The handle (which is a cheap flimsy plastic) gets blazing hot, hot enough to burn your hand when you try to open it. The plastic casing also gets blazing hot; I would expect it to get warm (like the last toaster I had) but this is so hot it heated up the kitchen like I had turned the big oven on with the door open. In addition, the toaster gives off a terrible burning plastic smell while it\'s on. Strong enough to fill my (small) apartment for 15 minutes. Also, a design issue: the round knobs look nice but there is no grippiness on them and they\'re perfectly round. You have to turn the toast timer dial past 10 minutes and then back to shorter time to toast (like most toasters), but because the knob is smooth and round, it\'s difficult to turn the knob back. Another design issue: there\'s no governor to stop the door, so when you open it then slide your fingers off, the handle smacks into the countertop. The only way to stop it would be to grab the glass part of the door and gently ease it onto the counter, but the glass is dangerously hot once the toaster has been on, so there\'s no way to stop the slam. Can\'t imagine that would be good for the structural integrity of the door over time. Sent it back immediately.'),
(3929, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Great Customer Service I received a Keurig Brewing system for Christmas.  About 6 months later, it began to malfunction.  I called customer service and was able to talk to a representative very quickly.  After going through a few steps to try to resolve the problem, the CSR said they would send out a new upgraded brewing system.  In less than a week I had a new system.  I have nothing but wonderful things to say about Keurig\'s customer service.  Since no one else in my household drinks coffee, I love being able to make a single cup rather than a whole pot.  I also use it to make ice tea which is excellent.  I have not made a whole pot of coffee yet, but it is nice to know that I have that capability.  I think the pods are a little expensive, but I do not waste any coffee by making whole pot and then throwing most of it away.Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(3930, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-14', 'Amazing blender! Works as well as my ninja! I had a ninja in the past and moved into a small apartment so I needed something smaller to use on my protein shakes. This truly works well. I was super impressed. Be careful though, the lid on my cup did end up breaking so I would advise you to be careful'),
(3931, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'Fantastic Coffee Maker In the past I\'ve always regarded Hamilton Beach products as pretty so-so; not bad but not great either.  This coffee-maker, however, is just great!!  Hamilton Beach has really come up with a superbly designed product.  The swing-out basket is very convenient.  While I liked the idea of a lift-out water container, I was concerned that the water might leak through the seal;  not a problem!!!  Have had it for almost  a year and its hasn\'t leaked a drop!  Love the convenience of the water container.  The little wheels on the bottom allow you to easily move the coffee maker around on the counter even while the coffee is brewing.  I also use it to heat water for tea and, unless I use a highly aromatic coffee, I get no coffee taste in my tea water even if I just rinse the pot and the coffee basket with water.  The controls are very simple and convenient to use.  Best coffee maker I\'ve ever had (and I\'ve had plenty)!!!'),
(3932, 3, 1, 4, '2015-01-05', 'Looks very nice. I have not used it much it requires ... Looks very nice.  I have not used it much it requires too fast maneuvering to set functions.  I have the toaster working and it is good.  Also wish the grill shelf automatically opened when you open the door.  Would have liked a light on inside.'),
(3933, 2, 1, 4, '2015-09-06', 'Four Stars The controls are hard to understand, and sometimes I think I\'ve turned it off, but I haven\'t.'),
(3934, 5, 1, 4, '2015-06-03', 'The idea of being able to remove and clean the ... The idea of being able to remove and clean the water reservoir is a BIG plus to this coffee maker for me.  The one thing I can truly complain about is it makes a lot of noise at the very end of its cycle.'),
(3935, 11, 1, 2, '2014-09-09', 'Two Stars Not what I had hoped it would be.  too much of a hassle for my 82 year old mom'),
(3936, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-26', 'Five Stars Makes coffee.'),
(3937, 8, 1, 4, '2014-03-10', 'A simple coffeemaker This is the simplest coffeemaker on market, I guess. It works as described. very simple coffeemaker. easy to use. I hope it can last long.'),
(3938, 5, 1, 4, '2014-01-11', 'I really like this Makes great coffee, programmable and good looks. We bought this to replace an old coffee maker that had stopped working. I really love the blue led light display not that this has anything to do with how well it works. The filter basket opens with a touch of a button so that you can lift out the basket to dump the old filter and coffee. The water reservoir at the back lifts off so that you can take it to the sink to fill up. So much easier than trying to gauge the little hole to pour water into. Great features and good coffee at an affordable price.'),
(3939, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-07', 'Wonderful oven. I use it all the time and ... Wonderful oven. I use it all the time and it does a great job and so much easier and cooler than using the big gas oven for small baking. Holds a 9 by12 cake pan and some 12 cup muffin pans. It really needs a back-light to make programming easier but everything else is great.'),
(3940, 8, 1, 5, '2015-10-13', 'coffee brewer I actually do like the scent it gives out when brewing coffee.'),
(3941, 5, 1, 1, '2015-05-13', 'Very poor quality machine. I am not one to write negative reviews but this started malfunctioning just over a month of having it. It was randomly starting at different times and has ruined a lot of coffee from having to refill it and reset it. The seller directed me to the manufacturer. I was not happy. Amazon is helping me to make the return. I do not recommend this at all. I ordered a Cuisinart programmable machine to replace it. Model DCC-1200.'),
(3942, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-29', 'Five Stars Great!.'),
(3943, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-01', 'The coffee maker did everything I expected it to do. A great machine for making a single cup of coffee. All you must do is read and follow the instructions that came with it.'),
(3944, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'We love you guys We called customer service for repair advice on our old Keurig coffee maker, and, \"SURPRISE\" They sent us a brand new replacement. We love you guys. We are dedicated to the KEURIG brand and have already told many of our friends and customers how we feel!'),
(3945, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-03', 'this is a great toaster. its being used in an office so ... this is a great toaster.  its being used in an office so lots of different people use it throughout the day and its so far handling the traffic well.  Its also attractive on the counter.'),
(3946, 5, 1, 4, '2014-09-04', 'Good product with 1 flaw The coffee maker is nice and works well.  The multiple settings for heat and strength are also convenient. I like that the water reservoir is removable.  The biggest problem is with the carafe.  There is a thick plastic rim around it (seemingly to protect the glass and make pouring easier).  However, the plastic rim makes it awkward to clean and difficult to empty all of the water when drying.  I may be a bit OCD about this which is why I still gave 4 stars but it\'s a bit annoying.'),
(3947, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-17', 'Five Stars Easy to store and works great'),
(3948, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-14', 'Five Stars practical and useful for small things and smoothies special'),
(3949, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-07', 'I\'m Pleasently Surprised I\'ve owned nothing but Krups coffee makers for the last 20 years and have become distressed at their decline in quality.  My original Krups lasted 12 years, but the newer ones last a couple years at most.  My current one was on it\'s last legs, and we were having all kinds of problems with it.  A $90.00 coffee maker should really work well and last a long time.  I did a lot of research on the best coffee makers & brewstations, and there were so many negative comments it was unbelievable.  Consumer Reports tested a lot of brewers and listed Mr. Coffee as one of their top picks.  Give me a break. I\'ve been there.  Mr. Coffee\'s don\'t produce pleasant coffee.  The Cuisinarts have serious mechanical problems & I called their customer service line to find out what they were doing to solve the broken latch problem on the lid and their answer to me was \"Don\'t worry about that.  If it breaks, we\'ll send you another unit.\"  I pointed out all the negative reviews to him & his response wasn\'t \"we\'re in process of fixing it,\" it was \"Those people don\'t know how to use our coffee maker.\"  I discovered those top-end makers that cost $200-500.00 that are the only 2 that are certified by some American coffee institute, but really, $200.00 for a coffee maker that\'s hand made by Norwegians that only has an on/off switch, no clock, no programmable features.  No way!  Did you know you can buy a Melitta filter cone for $5.00 that sits on top of  any pot or mug, that you pour boiling water into & presto, you\'ll have one of the best tasting cups of coffee you\'ve ever had.  But it doesn\'t have automatic controls, except for you & me - we\'re the controls. So I saw this Hamilton Beach maker with a high star rating, read the reviews ( yes, all of them), and for $45.00 I was willing to give it a try, though not expecting wonders.  I am impressed!  This is a well-engineered unit, from the nifty wheels below the base to allow you to rotate it to pull off the water reservoir, to the button controlled grounds basket popping out sideways, to the adjustable temperature warming plate, to the selectable brew strength, to the unique rim of the pot that makes it just about impossible to drip.  But all those are secondary to what everyone wants - good tasting coffee.  My son, who is a Starbucks fan and quite picky about coffee flavor, tasted my first pot of coffee and said \"Wow, this is good!\"  It is good.  It\'s not the best coffee I\'ve ever had, but it is very, very good - better than my Krups made by far.  Yes, and for only $45.00.  So no Norwegian craftsmen needed in this house. One word of warning.  I saw this unit had free shipping - cool!  I wanted to buy the permanent gold-toned filter also and I saw part way down the Amazon order page that for a small amount extra, I could get the maker & the cone together.  Ok, that\'s what I clicked on.  Guess what - when you click that link you\'ll pay $17.00 for shipping that you\'d save if you ordered the parts separately.  Really, Amazon, do you have to resort to tricking your customers that way?  I feel screwed.  Yes I should have read the invoice more carefully, but I do feel like Amazon screwed me.  Not good customer service, guys. Ok, here\'s an update after about 3 weeks of use.  I love it, love it, love it!  It\'s inexpensive, has plenty of extras, coffee is great tasting, and I would advise using the  brew strength setting of 1-4 cups for optimal flavor.  This product is superb!  Some have complained about the lit display being too bright.  Think dim nite light. I don\'t sleep in my kitchen & I sure don\'t know anyone who does.  The one thing about Krups machines that bugged me every day was how hard it was for a visually deficient \'ol codger like me to read what the current settings were on the display.  The Hamilton Beach lit display is big, crisp, and illuminated, perfect for my dim eyes.  Because the basket is one of those flat-bottomed types, it\'s not as efficient as the cones in extracting coffee flavor.  You\'ll need to use about 50% more grounds than with a cone-shaped filter.  I found that 1/2 cup grounds to 8 cups water was perfect for my taste buds.'),
(3950, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-05', 'Toasting paradise I had basically this exact same toaster oven for a few years until one of the heating elements broke. I was never thrilled with the way it toasted. This one is a huge improvement! I\'m not sure what they did to it, but the toasting feature is much much more even. Hurrah! My only complaint is there should be a way to cancel out the toasting if the bread is toasted before it dings besides forcibly turning the knob to off.'),
(3951, 9, 1, 2, '2015-09-17', 'Short Power Cord! We\'ve had 4 of these and they work great.  The one we just received has a ridiculously short power cord. If placed under a cabinet it must be unplugged or attached to an extension cord.  This is just one more example of manufactured products be cheapened to the point that hey are almost useless.'),
(3952, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-14', 'Works fine. Works fine. No complaints. It\'s a toaster....'),
(3953, 9, 1, 1, '2016-01-14', 'Quite possibly the most ridiculous coffee maker power cord design I have ever seen. This quite possibly is the most ridiculous coffee maker power cord design I have ever seen.  I was so excited to receive this and begin using it, followed the start up instructions, cleaned the tank, soaked the filter and when I was ready to plug it in, I was flabbergasted.  The cord, as you can see by the attached photo is about 2 1/2 inches in length from coffee maker to outlet.  I thought it was a power cord that extended to the desired length, but when it wasn\'t budging, I searched the product guide and found \"Special Cord Set Instruction\", which reads \"A short power-supply cord is provided to reduce the risks resulting from becoming entangled in or tripping over a longer cord.  Extension cords may be used if care is exercised in their use.\"  This is quite possibly the most ridiculous thing I have ever seen as if it is so much safer to use an extension cord???  I refuse to attach an extension cord to a beautiful coffee maker in my beautiful kitchen due to their product misfit design.  So with that said, I didn\'t actually get to use the product, so I cannot comment on the coffee that it makes, but the design is worth giving this product a 1.  I am also sadly disappointed that no where in the product description on the outside of the box does it indicate a useless power cord or I would have never purchased this product to begin with.'),
(3954, 7, 3, 5, '2015-09-08', 'We are very pleased with the Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffeemaker, Model 49995. We have a Keurig and bought the new coffeemaker for our motorhome - there is no difference in performance and the Hamilton Beach is \"half\" the price of a Keurig. Highly recommend this product.'),
(3955, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Five Stars Wife loves it she\'s happy!!'),
(3956, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-28', 'Makes a very good cup of coffee What I discovered after I bought it. 1. Louder by far then my old Keurig. 2. Can\'t turn it off between brews, unless you unplug it. 3. Had to buy new \"fill your own pod\" cups so that they fit. 4. Makes a very good cup of coffee. 5. Should have read more reviews, I may have not bought it.'),
(3957, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-06', 'wonderful and time efficient Toaster works fast!  The power and heat that comes from this toaster oven is amazing!'),
(3958, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-29', 'Great tasting bold coffee (there\'s a specific setting for that) We\'ve had a Bunn in years past and I wasn\'t impressed. The single cup makers didn\'t interest me for lots of reasons...cost of the single cups, inconvenience of making one cup at a time (in a 4-5 cup household) and no need for a big variety of flavored coffees, teas, etc. The HB ticks all the boxes for us. Great tasting bold coffee (there\'s a specific setting for that), filtered water, removable water tank so you don\'t have to fill and pour the coffee carafe, programmable timer to wake to the smell and sound (kinda loud) of coffee brewing. Not a big footprint to take up counter space and looks nice from the front, since the coffee pot is a permanent fixture out on our kitchen counter. Overall, a really good coffee maker if you\'re just looking for consistently well-brewed coffee.'),
(3959, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'Makes the greatest coffee of any coffee maker I ever had. Very pleased.  I had the older model of this type for over three years before it finally failed.  I was so pleased with small changes in this new unit.  Hope it lasts as long or longer.'),
(3960, 10, 1, 3, '2015-05-30', 'fired up from second time using it powerful and does a great job but from the second time i tried it it started sparkling fire from below i stopped using it since then.. i dont know whats the problem :('),
(3961, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-28', 'my boyfriend loves it I bought this for my boyfriend and he loves it. He did not have a toaster oven and was using a regular oven for cheese toast. One knob came off and heat is not even, though. The back side seems to be hotter. I use an older model of Black and Decker toaster oven, and it shuts of if I open the door. But this one does not shut off.'),
(3962, 2, 1, 1, '2015-01-04', 'Toaster Oven Dangerous Toaster worked great new but within 3 months the toast setting worked only once in a while and would not trip off the heating coil. Had to unplug it to shut off the heat. Unfortunately we held it too long and now can not return it. Good thing is it was inexpensive.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(3963, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'Great coffee, no leaks This coffee maker is excellent. I\'ve had it about a month now. The coffee is consistently tasty, and the pot never leaks! I\'d recommend this product to anyone, and so far it seems like a great value for the price.'),
(3964, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Would highly recommend purchasing the 2.0 Keurig The 2.0 is great for when we have company. Since we can brew a pot. I have had 2 other Keurig units and as of now this is by far my favorite brewer. Would recommend highly. I also order coffee direct from Keurig get great prices & discounts...'),
(3965, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-18', 'Excellent Quality I don\'t use this often but when I have it actually fits 6 pieces of toast & works great! The price is an unbelievable value, I had a very expensive toaster oven that I gave up in my dissolution & this is equally good at a fraction of the price!'),
(3966, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-27', 'what I like. I really like the fact that I can put a lot of the parts in the top rack of the dish washer.'),
(3967, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Five Stars Easy to use not complicated Makes great toast.'),
(3968, 12, 1, 5, '2016-05-15', 'Five Stars works as expected'),
(3969, 5, 1, 2, '2014-09-23', 'Two Stars Cheap plastic. Broke down after just 1 year of irregular usage.'),
(3970, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-29', 'Five Stars Very good.'),
(3971, 12, 1, 5, '2014-02-15', 'My Second Toastation What a great gift to myself. This machine does it all, toasts, bakes, keeps food warm. It\'s just the right size, easy to keep clean and is pretty in red. I will buy a third oven when the time comes. I can\'t live without it. Enjoy! Peace'),
(3972, 2, 1, 1, '2016-05-28', 'I returned it. It is a fire hazard! ... I returned it. It is a fire hazard!! I would have given it no stars but there was not an option for that.'),
(3973, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-20', 'In a blink of an eye .... goop :/ I thoroughly enjoy getting a cup of coffee at the blink of an eye! But, I don\'t like having to clean the coffee ground goop out of the needle every 15-20 brews! I got my Keurig 2.0 K200 for free to test use and review! #HelloKeurig'),
(3974, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Five Stars Outstanding unit!'),
(3975, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'Five Stars Excellent, does everything it\'s suppose to do'),
(3976, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-15', 'Love that when u open the door the tray pops ... Love that when u open the door the tray pops out for easier access to your meal. We had one for the last 10 years this was a replacement because we love the product!.'),
(3977, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-29', 'She seems very satisfied and has stated she loves it several times Posting on behalf of my wife who is the coffee drinker on our family.  She seems very satisfied and has stated she loves it several times.'),
(3978, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Love my new Keurig Love my new Keurig! First Keurig I have bought and I am so glad I invested in it. Totally worth it. Runs perfectly. So efficient. Completely satisfied! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(3979, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'good looking easy to use works great - great price ... good looking easy to use works great - great price - way better than the one i got last time at walmart.'),
