(3981, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-26', 'Good Value. Does the job. Operates well. I do wish that the drip pan was wider though.'),
(3982, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-04', '... that we\'ve had for a couple years now and love it! We have one that we\'ve had for a couple years now and love it! :) not too big but we\'ve definitely used it a lot, especially in the summer when I want to bake and turning on the oven just makes the kitchen and family room too warm. Toaster oven is perfect it!! :)'),
(3983, 3, 1, 3, '2015-04-05', 'This is basically a good appliance. It looks good This is basically a good appliance. It looks good, fits nicely on the counter. It is sometimes hard to change the preset timer and oven settings....or maybe it\'s just me .It bakes well and broils well.'),
(3984, 11, 1, 3, '2014-08-09', 'My mom has been using it almost daily so it must be pretty easy to use I ordered this for my 82 year old mom a month ago. She likes it overall but wishes it were higher to give more space between top and bread pan. She is still getting used to all the features. My mom has been using it almost daily so it must be pretty easy to use.'),
(3985, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-16', 'Five Stars Great little toaster'),
(3986, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-12', 'Like the toaster oven for a lot of the cooking Like the toaster oven for a lot of the cooking. Quick for items for lunch and etc. for a couple'),
(3987, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-22', 'Excellent Excellent'),
(3988, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-21', 'Don\'t waste your Money All I wanted was a toaster to toast bread evenly.  This piece of #@%! doesn\'t even come close.  All the reviews that said one side is burnt or nearly black while the other side hasn\'t even begun to change color are spot on.'),
(3989, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-01', 'Five Stars Works great'),
(3990, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-06', 'Nice pot. I like the fact it rolls out ... Nice pot. I like the fact it rolls out easy and you can remove the back water reservoir to fill if you want. Very happy with this purchase'),
(3991, 5, 1, 4, '2016-03-09', 'GOOD BUY! Great coffee maker. Easy to use and keeps your coffee HOT! I like the compact design. I don\'t think you can beat it for the price. One downside is that they recommend a replaceable filter but do not include the filter or the filter holder with the unit. You have to buy that separately. Doesn\'t that stink?'),
(3992, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-24', 'reheat things like pizza(the microwave make it soggy) and to put a ... I bought this to make toast, reheat things like pizza(the microwave make it soggy) and to put a few spoonfuls of raw chocolate chip cookie dough in  it for  a hot cookie snack.  It\'s perfect for all those things.'),
(3993, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-17', 'Favorite Features of any Coffee Maker to Date Looks nice and works well. My testing indicates that liquid in the brew cup reaches a max of 180F so it doesn\'t get to the recommended 200F, but I\'m not finding a home model auto drip maker that does. It still gets the coffee hotter than other coffee makers I\'ve had, so the flavor turns out better versus past coffee makers. Brew time depends on the starting water temperature but it also brews faster than other makers I\'ve had which likely relates to the higher brew temperature. The blue display has a nice look without being too bright since only the digits are lit against a dark blue background. I bought it mainly for the swing out filter basket and removable water bin to make it easier to use without moving out from under the cabinet overhang. The narrow width also maximizes counter space. It has the typical timer as well as a brew strength control which pauses the water addition to give more extraction time but note that doesn\'t result in hotter water.The adjustable hot plate temperature keeps the coffee from burning before returning for refills as well.'),
(3994, 5, 1, 1, '2015-09-24', 'A lemon. I thought this was a great product until it completely stopped working after five months. The company will only refund or replace within 30 days. I do not recommend this coffeemaker.'),
(3995, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-14', 'Five Stars I love this coffee pot'),
(3996, 12, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Jack of all trades, master of none. I do love this toaster (for us)!  We make toast all the time, and occasionally use the oven part for melting cheese on a sandwich or pizza.  Its small, lightweight, and decent for the price.  It\'s also adorable. For you, be warned: I don\'t imagine this would withstand heavy use for years. Also, thinner slices of toast tend to lean back in the toaster, browning the back more than the front.  Very deceiving! There isn\'t a way to set a timer when it\'s on the oven settings (at least not that I\'ve found?), So set an external timer, or just watch it!'),
(3997, 8, 1, 1, '2016-08-26', 'Disappointed! The Black one did say in the description that it was a 6 cup unit but the picture was 12 cups. Disappointed!.'),
(3998, 12, 1, 5, '2014-05-12', 'Toasts and Heats! This was a replacement for an earlier model of the same...in constant use, the original lasted over 5 years!  I\'ll probably order another in 5 years.  Easy to use, simple dial handles and quick heat..'),
(3999, 5, 1, 1, '2016-02-02', 'Someone contact me on how to replace this piece of crud coffee pot stopped working today and no way to contact seller. Says I cant return.. I haven\'t even had this for 60 days and it doesn\'t work $42 for junk'),
(4000, 12, 1, 4, '2014-01-05', 'Not sure I get the negative reviews We\'ve had this toaster oven for years. It is looking a little worn now so was looking to buy a new one. The newer model may or may not be better -- so if looking to replace read the reviews of the new version carefully. As for this working - it works. The oven is for warming things up (not cooking) and the toaster part does it\'s job well. Maybe folks expectations are just too much - it\'s not like this is a $100+ oven. If you want something to head up quickly something like Pizza (rather than using a Mwave) to get the crispy crust back or frozen items like french fries it\'s great. If you are thinking of using it as a substitute for a real oven -- maybe not so much. Never had an issue.'),
(4001, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-14', 'packaged nice, I ordered for my sister in law as ... Shipped right away, packaged nice, I ordered for my sister in law as she wanted something easy to use and not have to heat up the oven to keep the house cooler in the summer. She loves it and I do have to say I ordered because of an awesome review where a guy had a video that showed all the bells and whistles...there are some nice features on this oven.'),
(4002, 7, 3, 5, '2016-03-01', 'I\'ve had this five days now and can\'t say enough how much I love this! I had a Keurig and it was acting up....water leaking, not brewing a full cup so decided to toss it and get a new one. I researched coffee makers and decided on this one and am so happy I chose this one. It was a toss up btwn another Hamilton Beach which was more expensive. This one allows you to brew water for tea also which was what I wanted too. A++'),
(4003, 7, 3, 3, '2014-08-18', 'Coffee doesn\'t come out as hot as I would prefer.'),
(4004, 5, 1, 3, '2015-12-20', 'OK Coffee maker, but requires more coffee to get a good pot I felt that the coffee brewed was not as strong as it should have been.  I actually put it in storage and purchased a Mr. Coffee brand which met my expectations as to the amount of coffee grinds needed to make a good pot of coffee.'),
(4005, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-27', 'Can still trust the B&D brand (unlike many others) Glad to get rid of a standard toaster that either popped up too soon to stayed down until the toast burned. This is well designed for toasting and baking/warming items you might not want to stick in the microwave like leftover pizza slices.'),
(4006, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Five Stars Works well.'),
(4007, 4, 1, 3, '2016-03-17', 'Element died after 3 years Element died after 3 years.  We bought this in September 2012 and the lower element just died.  The oven worked well but I hoped for a longer life.'),
(4008, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'My blender just got here nicely pack, and I love it I just made ... My blender just got here nicely pack, and I love it I just made a blueberry smoothie it blended real good, but you can smell it.'),
(4009, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Five Stars Great product'),
(4010, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-15', 'Good coffee maker Small, simple and cheap.  What more do you want from a coffee maker.'),
(4011, 2, 1, 3, '2016-03-22', 'Toasts well, but easy to burn your hand on, be careful! This toaster over does toast nicely, but where the handle mounts to the door, behind the grab part of the handle is the exposed glass of the door, which gets HOT, and is easy to touch when you are opening the oven after use.  Be careful.  I feel it\'s a design flaw and should be addressed, but otherwise the oven functions well.'),
(4012, 4, 1, 2, '2016-10-26', 'Faulty Heating Element Like many others have pointed out, the bottom heating element warped on mine after 3.5 years. Really like this toaster oven, but I will be purchasing a different brand to replace this one.'),
(4013, 12, 1, 4, '2016-01-08', 'Great but burns food quickly I love my new toaster oven but it does burn food very easily if you\'re not careful. I have tried to reheat rolls in this and it burnt the tops of them because the rack is so close to the heating element. Now I just make sure to put it on about 250 degrees to reheat things to avoid burnt food. The toaster part works great for me. No problems with that.'),
(4014, 5, 1, 4, '2014-09-21', 'The poor thing sounds like it just gave birth all the features that have been in reviews are valid, and, I appreciate them.  However, the clatter that this model makes at the end of the brewing is extremely loud.  The poor thing sounds like it just gave birth! I hesitate to make coffee while guests are still asleep worrying that it will wake them.'),
(4015, 4, 1, 1, '2015-10-21', 'Loved it until it almost BURNED THE HOUSE DOWN I absolutely loved this toaster.  Besides a VERY loud beep when it was done, it was the perfect size. After almost 2 years of great use, THE BOTTOM BURNER WILL NOT TURN OFF, EVEN WHEN THE DEVICE IS OFF.  I made some muffins in the morning and in the afternoon I tried to bake something, but it wouldn\'t turn off.  The heat was way past the \"temperature,\" so we just turned it off.  It CONTINUED to heat.  We had to unplug it.  Please read the other reviews who have had similar problems, and ignore the initial positive reviews for people who haven\'t owned it long.  I took it apart, and it is unfixable, so I\'m very disappointed.  I will not buy it again- it is way too dangerous as a flaw. Good luck and steer clear of this one!!'),
(4016, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Love my K250 Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.  My daughter and I both love our new Keurig we use it numerous times daily.  I have found that there are a number of different flavors that I like.  Thank you so much for such an awesome product.'),
(4017, 9, 1, 2, '2015-12-08', 'I liked the features on this one so I decided try ... This is the second Cuisinart coffee maker I have had, both leaked out the bottom.  I liked the features on this one so I decided try a Cuisinart again.  I have only had this one a short while and have to clean up a water puddle after each use.  Very disappointed.'),
(4018, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-03', 'Hamilton Beach 46201 12 Cup This by far the best one so far No spill and keeps coffee very hot I would highly recommend this unit'),
(4019, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-25', 'Good Value Black and Decker Toaster Oven is efficient and meets all of our basic needs for a toaster oven.  The toasting function works well once you determine the proper settings for how dark you like your toast.'),
(4020, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-28', 'Five Stars for the price this is a very good oven.'),
(4021, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-15', 'Five Stars perfect'),
(4022, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'The convenience and flavor are pretty hard to beat I have had Keurigs for over five years. The convenience and flavor are pretty hard to beat. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for the review. .'),
(4023, 10, 1, 1, '2016-01-22', 'Pass on this It smelled odd when I received it. Like a chemical sort of smell. I tried using it until my order of a better blender came in, and it broke- cracked!  Hardly got to use it at all.  Don\'t waste your money.'),
(4024, 6, 1, 3, '2014-03-11', 'Disappointed I guess it is hard to find a good toaster for under $100.  This works but dosen\'t toast evenly and I still have not totally figured out the time for toasting various things.  It is okay for the price, though.'),
(4025, 11, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Five Stars Nice toaster oven works great luv it easy to use.'),
(4026, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-13', 'Update: Exchanged product is excellent, especially for the price I wrote below 3 star review when I received the first product. Seller contacted me immediately, apologized for the \"faulty\" product and sent me a new one. I honestly hadn\'t thought the first product was faulty. I just thought \"This is what you get for the low price\" But the second toaster (identical product) I received has none of the issues the first one has so I\'m upgrading my review to 5 stars, especially considering the very low price it has. Previous Review (3 stars) Pros: 1. Cheap 2. Toasts & Warms Cons: 1. Smokes like a little chimney, no joke. 2. Exterior gets so hot, you\'ll def. jump couple of times moving around the kitchen until you learn your lesson:) 3. Power cord is very short, I get it, it\'s a kitchen appliance but come on, that short?'),
(4027, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-26', 'Five Stars This Toaster Oven is just what we needed works great.'),
(4028, 10, 1, 4, '2015-08-26', 'Great, but cracks happen I bought this blender, to take my smoothies to work with me. It was great for a few months, I loved the sip spout on the lid it was nice to just blend and go. But unfortunately one slip/drop I got a huge crack down the side and couldn\'t use it anymore.'),
(4029, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-23', 'The top broke! It worked great for a while, I made several shakes, but then that black thing on top broke! That was disappointing. I guess this thing is made with flimsy materials.'),
