(4034, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-27', 'Perfectttt! The Hamilton Beach 22708 Toastation 2-Slice is perfect for quickly making toast, no-oil-added grilled cheese and veggie burger sandwiches.'),
(4035, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-30', 'Nice Blender Wonderful little blender. Just what I needed.'),
(4036, 7, 3, 5, '2017-01-10', 'It has worked great the last month. no complaints.'),
(4037, 2, 1, 3, '2016-06-23', 'Nice and A bit noisy. Nice and small'),
(4038, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-07', 'Five Stars Haven\'t even used it yet and purchased it months ago. Looks simple though, makes coffee.'),
(4039, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-18', 'Smoke Colored Water Reservoir I ordered this specific coffee maker because my other one died.  I absolutely loved my original one.  I really like this one, as far as functionality - swivel base,blue clock timer that I can actually see, programmable, etc.  However, I was disappointed that the water reservoir was a smoky color, making it difficult for me to see the water line for filling it.  The previous one was clear and I absolutely fell in love with it.  So easy to see.  Unfortunately, I had thrown away my old one, so I\'m having to learn to live with the obscured smoky color.  But, please, \"if it ain\'t broke, don\'t fix it\".  It wasn\'t broken and this fix is not so good.'),
(4040, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'I like this toaster over so much I like this toaster over so much, I bought it again when the other one died from so much use.'),
(4041, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-10', 'I\'m living alone and it\'s nice to not need to warm up the oven to ... Works well, I\'m living alone and it\'s nice to not need to warm up the oven to cook a couple of pieces of chicken or naan.'),
(4042, 4, 1, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Cusinart Custom Classic Toaster Oven does everything advertised  Timer works perfectly.'),
(4043, 4, 1, 1, '2016-07-17', 'Fire hazard One of the heating rods has warped and cracked open. Also, the oven does not turn off automatically when you open the door to remove food after it is done cooking, and there is no warning that the oven is still on. It\'s not worth it to me to return the Cuisinart or have it fixed. I have bought a Breville as a replacement.'),
(4044, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-12', 'Five Stars best toster oven ever.'),
(4045, 3, 1, 5, '2014-05-14', 'Convection oven Absolutely the best investment I ever made. It performs beautifully and toasts better than my expensive toaster. Now I use it for both. Can cook a small meal with no problem thanks to convection. Solid buy!'),
(4046, 5, 1, 1, '2015-11-02', 'Not a happy customer at this time. We had to send it back to Hamilton Beach because it didn\'t seem to keep our coffee hot .  We are suppose to get a replacement from the company.'),
(4047, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-07', 'Five Stars I love this thing and use it all the time but should have gotten a bigger one'),
(4048, 12, 1, 1, '2016-05-07', '... got this toaster oven to safe space and I liked the way it looked I got this toaster oven to safe space and I liked the way it looked. The toaster part is fine, however the oven is useless everything burns..it got bad reviews and I took a chance anyway. BIG MISTAKE. how can u sell an item like this.  already used it so can t send back. Hamilton Beach should PAY me to keep it. M Daniels'),
(4049, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-29', 'Good but not perfect! We just recently purchased the Keurig 2.0 and were so excited to start using it until we discovered that many of the k-cups we had in stock would not work in this machine.  What a major disappointment!  We have since learned how to do the extra step but find it time consuming and should not be necessary.  This should have been worked out before placing this system in retail stores for public purchase.  On the positive side, it does brew nicely after having to wait for it to warm up in a rather noisy fashion.  We are an office of all females who really aren\'t inclined to be patient when caffeine is desperately needed!  Most other functions are easy to use and the carafe feature is a nice addition.  We have not yet eliminated our older Keurig brewer because it is easier to use at this point even though it is in its senior years of functioning AND it takes all brands of k-cups. Keep working on this Keurig Company and you will have even more amazing products!!!  We still support you!!  Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(4050, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Works great Works great, small footprint. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4051, 1, 1, 3, '2015-09-07', 'It does the job Meh. It brews coffee but only up to a 10oz. cup. If I want to fill a travel mug I have to run it twice. I elevate the machine because my two travel mugs won\'t fit under it even with the tray removed. I ordered this model just because of the color options. I\'ve had no trouble with the operations, everything runs smoothly. I do wish you wouldn\'t have to wait to press start till after it preheats. All in all I prefer to go next door and use my fathers older Keurig that I bought him for Xmas a few years ago.'),
(4052, 10, 1, 4, '2015-07-25', 'Quiet but little power This personal blender is the quietest one I have ever owned. It also blends great if you are doing lots of liquids. I tend to do a lot of green smoothies where I put in almond milk, frozen kale, frozen bananas, and frozen berries. Because everything is frozen I guess it gets heavy and I have to mix it with a spoon. Otherwise blends everything well.'),
(4053, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-21', 'If my last maker was Mr. Coffee... this is Dr. Coffee. I was impressed enough to buy two more. My favorite coffee maker so far. I\'m reluctant to be over-enthusiastic about a new purchase, because the a product\'s true quality shows over time. I\'m tired of feeling like coffee makers are disposable, but I\'m also not convinced that any coffee maker is worth $100 or more (except for makes like Bunn\'s commercial models). So... enter the sub-$50 price-bracket. The average \"standard\" coffee maker with a clock and timer is about $30. What does an extra $10-15 get you with the Hamilton Beach 46201? With the help of another reviewer, I see that cheaper makers sometimes utilize cheaper thermostat systems. The same high-heat that makes the water hot enough to extract coffee from the beans, also controls the temperature of the burner. The reviewer suggested this was a source of bitterness because the coffee at the bottom of the pot is burning. *shrug* I don\'t know about the science of thermodynamics, but I do know that coffee is tasting great out of this new pot I\'m reviewing here! The obvious benefits of this maker are the removable water tank (\"reservoir\" is too hard to spell)... the water tank is pretty cool. I didn\'t think I\'d be filling the maker by removing the tank, but as it turns out after a week of using it... this is what I do naturally. There is a nice lip which accommodates your grip easily, and after filling the tank by first filling the pot, and pouring in... I\'ve decided it\'s easiest to simply fill the maker as the designer\'s intended. If you have trouble accepting this and just want to flip open the lid and pour water in from the pot as you always have... well, it\'s MUCH easier to do that with this maker also! The tank lid flips open allowing a wide-open, unobstructed pour. My previous Mr. Coffee maker has a stupidly designed, complicated plastic grate that you have to pour water through... so I\'m doing a bit of a marksman pour... actually having to THINK about how I\'m pouring water into the maker (in the tired, wee-hours of the morning)... THIS maker... ends all that. I like the swing-out filter basket... and I really like STANDARD FILTERS! I went through the cone filter phase... nope, never again. I just never tasted the benefit. The filters cost more, and you have to sort of \"prep\" each filter that you use... whereas the normal filters fall in place effortlessly. I realize we\'re not talking about actual work here either way... but if there\'s no appreciable benefit to something that costs a little more and requires a little more effort... I\'ll take cheap, good, and easy... thank you very much. NO DRIP POT! The first time you pour a cup from this pot I guarantee you\'ll grin... Holy Smokes... why in the heck don\'t all manufacturers at least try to steal this no-drip pot design? The little bar of plastic that goes across the spout combines with the spout shape to make a perfect pour, every time. Hey Hamilton Beach! Do you want me to make a great commercial for this maker? I have lots of ideas :-) I also like the little wheels on the bottom of the maker. The Mr. Coffee maker this one is replacing had rubber \"no-slide\" feet. WHO leaves their maker tucked away so that it steams up the bottom of your wood cabinets? Nope, you pull it out a bit... the thing NEEDS to slide around. Hamilton Beach (or the designer of this maker) deserves a pat on the back for that little detail. The buttons stick out a bit, which I like more than the flush-buttons that seemed more of a style choice on my last maker. There\'s a positive \"tactile\" feel to them, not effort to push, but a satisfying \"click\" response. I\'ve had other makers with buttons that don\'t always react, or I had to push a specific part of the button. This is simple, and functional. I like things that simply work. The clock display is great. I prefer an LED where the numbers are lit vs. the background being lit. In normal household lighting, the clock is EASY to read. This is great for people of all ages. Also... notice the clock and all controls are at the TOP... vs the bottom of the maker, or running down one side. I\'m not usually a fan of extended warranties, but with my past-experience with Mr. Coffee (see my other reviews, I loved my last Mr. Coffee maker so much that I bought one for my Mom... Well... her\'s crapped out in about 3 months... and mine became \"problematic\" in roughly 9 months... so EXTENDED WARRANTY HERE I COME!)... Anyway, Canopy Warranty offered by Amazon was only $4. I\'m sure there will be a little BS involved if I ever make a claim, but here\'s hoping it goes well. I\'m hoping I never need the warranty, but for $4 I like the peace of mind. Here\'s the important point about this maker vs. the Mr. Coffee maker, which I was also enthusiastic about when I first got it... so much so, that I bought one for my Mom too. If that last maker was Mr. Coffee... THIS maker is Dr. Coffee. This make is so well-designed... so well thought-out... that I really WANT it to last 3 years! Mostly, I hope Hamilton Beach continues to offer a maker like this... at an \"every-man\" price. Asking roughly 25% more for a maker that\'s 100% better? That\'s easy money... I will gladly pay a little more for anything SMART. After 3 days of using this maker... I was so impressed with the design features that I bought two more, one for my Mom and one for my brother... both with the extended warranty. For the next 3 years we have a nice little product test pool going :-)'),
(4054, 9, 1, 3, '2015-01-25', 'good but your paying for a name good but your paying for a name, as my Mr. Coffee does just as good for 1/3 the price. The basket holder has already cracked, rendering the product useless. Replacement parts are grossly overpriced. If I could return it I would.'),
(4055, 6, 1, 3, '2014-07-20', 'Toast settings inconsistent Settings will sometimes toast bread just fine, at other times at the same setting the bread is barely toasted.  Otherwise works well.'),
(4056, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-24', 'Good for the money The blender meets my expectations for an inexpensive blender. It does the job, but with frozen fruit for smoothies, I do find myself opening and stirring a couple times, to help the blender get everything processed. Which is annoying, but I\'d rather do that than spend a couple hundred dollars on a blender. Everything can go in the dishwasher which is great.'),
(4057, 11, 1, 5, '2015-07-25', 'Five Stars wonderful'),
(4058, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-30', 'I like the compact size too This toaster does a very even job of making toast.  Both sides are golden brown.  I like the compact size too.  It fits right in my drawer so it doesn\'t clutter up my counters.  Another great product by Cuisinart!'),
(4059, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-15', 'Wow this is great. This new model has a \'cancel\' button to ... Wow this is great. This new model has a \'cancel\' button to eject the toast in case it\'s getting too toasted (the old, tired model that finally quit on us did not). The only thing I would like is a oven switch, separate from the temperature setting.'),
(4060, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Nice Very nice product!  I think the best buy.  I like that it had the removable water compartment.'),
(4061, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-12', 'Best deal for the money My first toaster oven. I LOVE it.  For larger items I will still use the regular oven but for potatoes and frozen items it works great. The price was the best. I looked at all of them. I would have spent 3 times the money but I didn\'t need to. It is just the right size for the counter. I pull it out a little when in use due to the heat. It heats up fast and also cools down fast. Easy to clean, easy to operate. What\'s not to like about this?.'),
(4062, 11, 1, 5, '2016-07-24', 'Graet product And Awesome deal ! 5 stars This is a terrific small oven. I got it for times when my large oven is in use with something I can\'t fit in with it or adjust the temperature for both items. Works well for casseroles, rolls, and canapes. I like that it will quickly broil a steak or lamb chop. I am very happy I bought it. would recommend to a friend.'),
(4063, 1, 1, 3, '2016-08-26', 'I got your K-cup right here. After at least 5-6 years, we gave up trying to limp along on our original Keurig. Enter KEURIG 2.0! A machine I was skeptical of from the start. This seemed like a trap. Like when an app you love has an \"update\", only to later find out they merely added ads and took away previously-free features. That\'s Keurig 2.0! PROS: - The motor doesn\'t make that horrid grinding sound that would wake the whole house each morning for every cup of coffee. This is almost entirely silent. - Range of sizes. We don\'t need carafes, just single cups. Maybe 3-4 a day. And sometimes hot water for cooking. - Fast warm-up and brew times. CONS: -Water bin location. It\'s on the back now, and the lid is shaped like a horseshoe. A bit wonky. -The k-cup monopoly conspiracy! This hateful machine only fancies \"Keurig brand\" k-cups. Not those \"Keurig compatible\" wannabes. Which I was unaware we even had until this thing started rejecting cups from our bin. And it doesn\'t like double-brewing a single k-cup. (Which you can trick it into doing by rotating the cup.) These are two things the original Keurig did without fail. It wasn\'t a feature, it was common sense. I should be able to use any Keurig-friendly cup as many times as I damn well please. But nope, Keurig 2.0 will have none of your funny business! One day, after rejecting the very last k-cup of my favorite tea, this thing almost went into the trash. Fortunately (?) I discovered for less than $10 I can buy a wee metal clip that somehow forces the brewer into using any k-cup again - SOMETHING IT SHOULD HAVE DONE BY DEFAULT. So, in summary: This brewer out-of-box = 3 stars. I hate their sudden proprietary nonsense. You are rich enough, sirs. Deal with it. This brewer + metal \"fix\" clip = 5 stars.'),
(4064, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-06', 'Five Stars It was a gift for my daughter and she loves it!'),
(4065, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-13', 'love the well made.  love the digital.'),
(4066, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-27', 'Quality toaster oven This a quality product. I had others but this one is probably the best quality. It heats well and very simple to use.'),
(4067, 5, 1, 1, '2014-09-19', 'The unit died after three brews. I sought and purchased this unit for our vacation rental property. I wanted a low cost, simple, reliable unit which all could use as an easy plug and play coffee maker. The specs met my requirements. I flushed the unit and used it three times to insure it was ready for its intended purpose. The first guest called unhappy that the unit was not working. I had our maintenance man buy a replacement from the local drug store. Of course I had to pay for another new unit and I had to pay the maintenance man for his trouble. Eventually I checked the dead Hamilton Beach. It appears an internal fuse blew. So much for its reliability. If you want trouble free reliability don\'t buy this unit.'),
(4068, 2, 1, 3, '2015-04-10', 'change one thing.... Works great BUT there is one feature I am not happy with, when you turn the timer dial off, if you go too far past the ding it sets the toaster to ON (with no timer). I would have rather they set the ON (with no timer) past the timer settings. This is an accident waiting to happen. Other than that it is a good product.'),
(4069, 6, 1, 4, '2014-02-13', 'Nice Quality Product This product exceeded my quality expectations.  However, on occasion it does toast bread unevenly.  I would recommend it to my friends and family.'),
(4070, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-12', 'Four Stars It did the job but I use it rarely as I never seem to need 4 slices any more.'),
(4071, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Works for me Read reviews before purchase.  Lot of negativity.  Took a chance and was pleasantly surprised.  Used a few rounds of some stale bread to burn off chemical smell, which you get with most high heat products when first used.  Been using now for two weeks at high setting to toast English muffins, and they toast perfectly.  Golden brown without drying out in under three minutes.  A bit uneven on the browning, but surface of muffins is uneven, so to be expected.  Toasts bread evenly even faster.  Easy to clean and store.'),
(4072, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-12', 'Four Stars My only complaint is that the cord is too short.'),
(4073, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-07', 'Quality I love this thing.  It\'s small enough to fit my counter, but big enough I can toast a couple of bagles in it.  It heats quickly and evenly and the buzzer is loud but not completely obnoxious.'),
(4074, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-13', 'One Star I\'ve had this for two weeks. It didn\'t blend well, and now it\'s suddenly stopped working :('),
(4075, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-30', 'Works well. Small print instructions. Works well.  Small print instructions.'),
(4076, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-13', 'Toaster Oven A+++ I love this toaster!  It works just like Black and Decker promises.  These are so handy to have in the kitchen.  It uses less Kilowatts than my kitchen stove.  I use it because it is great for leftovers, or toasting sandwiches.'),
(4077, 12, 1, 5, '2014-06-04', 'Long lasting quality toaster My mom owned an original one of these for over 10 years and had been searching for a new one after it got lost in a move. She says she loves the \'new\' cancel button and it works just as lovely as her old one.'),
(4078, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Quality product at a good price. Take care of it and this toaster ... Quality product at a good price.  Take care of it and this toaster will last many years.'),
(4079, 10, 1, 3, '2015-09-20', 'Read Product Description Carefully I was disappointed but it might be because I didn\'t read the details better. although it was single serve it seems too small a capacity for single serve. I also do not like that the stop does not come off for cleaning. This feature very inconvenient for wanting it to be clean and not soaking the bottom of the blender where the cord is. In addition, the blender doesn\'t chop even bananas quickly throughout the mixture.'),
(4080, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-23', 'One Star It broke after 3 days...oh well....'),
(4081, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-10', 'Super easy to use and brews quickly Super easy to use and brews quickly. I love the convenience but dislike the waste - accessories to reduce amount of waste are expensive. Occasionally there is a clog (that I have learned to clear via a YouTube video) that causes brewing to stop completely - about once a month. Overall, I am very satisfied with my decision to purchase this item. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(4082, 5, 1, 2, '2016-05-29', 'Arriving with a broken HOUR button takes the convenience right out of this machine.... After searching long and hard for a new coffee pot, we decided to take a chance from the good reviews on this machine and purchase one. Unfortunately, while trying to set it up we realized the HOUR button on the machine did not work, which means, we cannot set the AM/PM function on it, or program it to start brewing at a certain time. Which unfortunately is one of the main reasons we bought it. Before we tried to program it for the next day, we had made our morning pot and it made a good cup of coffee.While we weren\'t expecting lightning speed, it was a little slow to fill the pot, but tasted great. Living on a small island in Alaska, makes sending this back more work than its worth, so I don\'t know what we will be doing. Either  we will be back to looking for another pot, going back to our tiny 4 cup pot we were so excited to be done with, or just making due. I\'ve never had many issues with amazon until recently, I\'m hoping this is a fluke and not a trend of unforeseen complications like my last few orders.'),
(4083, 2, 1, 4, '2016-06-20', 'Four Stars Still getting use to it.'),
(4084, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-04', 'Perfect ! I can eat delicious toast everyday ! this price is so reasonable . I\'m so happy, thanks !'),
(4085, 12, 1, 5, '2016-10-17', 'Perfect Perfect size for toasting and baking.'),
(4086, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-13', 'Great coffee maker Great coffee maker.  Fantastic delivery. So nice to just get one cup and have rest keep warm for 2nd cup!'),
(4087, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-16', 'Great toaster oven! Love this toaster!  I have one in each of our homes _'),
(4088, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-31', 'Five Stars Great for cooking small items without having to turn the huge oven on for!'),
(4089, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-03', 'Five Stars Good, we like it'),
(4090, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-11', 'Perfect cup of coffee I recently recieved this product free for testing and I love it. It has the ability for filtered water which is great cause we all know how gross tap is, but if you can\'t afford the filters they aren\'t required to make a cup o joe. The option for strong coffee really hooked me. I like it robust and strong so this system is perfect. It also has the option for karafe brewing which really suits my bf and I.  We love our coffee so 4 cups at a time are perfecto. The only thing I wish it had was a timed brew so that when I\'m up for work it is ready instead of waiting for it to preheat.'),
(4091, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-22', 'Five Stars This oven toaster is very easy to use and clean. Great buy! THanks!'),
(4092, 11, 1, 1, '2014-06-27', 'The \"Black\" in Black and Decker stands for what your toast looks like The \"Black\" in Black and Decker stands for what your toast looks like regardless of how low you set the toast setting.  The \"even\" in \"eventoast technology \" stands for the even blackness of your toast.  If there was a number less than one star that\'s what I would give it.  Don\'t even think of giving this as a gift.'),
(4093, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-15', 'Five Stars Was a gift'),
(4094, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-10', 'Great value Great product. Have had for a yr love the 2 in 1.'),
(4095, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-22', 'Handy Machine I really enjoy using my Keurig very much! I am not an avid coffee drinker, but with college quickly approaching this fall, I\'ve begun to get in the habit of using this wonderful machine almost daily. The coffee is good (I do add lots of cream). I have tried variety of beverages, such as hot and iced coffees, iced teas, cocoas as well as strawberry lemonade. The one thing that bothers me with this machine is that it makes some odd noises while functioning, despite claiming that it is a new and improved quieter machine. I will continue to use my Keurig and hope that it lasts for many years to come. Thank you Keurig for the completely free pods for this review!'),
(4096, 5, 1, 4, '2016-07-28', 'Great value for the money Great value for the money. So far, no issues. It is a nice looking unit that makes great coffee.'),
(4097, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-24', 'This is a great coffee maker We have had a Hamilton beach for years and loved the detachable reservoir.  We chose Hamilton Beach for our new coffee maker and like it even more than the old one.  Coffee is great and it easy to make with the detachable reservoir.  It is also easier to clean with some new design features in the way its made.  This one also has several options on the way the coffee is brewed to allow it to be tailored to your taste.'),
(4098, 11, 1, 3, '2014-05-01', 'Go bigger This is a nice little oven. Doesn\'t really do a good job on toast but it works. It\'s just to small, not by much but it\'s awkward.  Little deeper, little taller would be perfect. Get the next size up, I will next time.'),
(4099, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-25', 'One Star Disappointed. Not what I expected. .'),
(4100, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'I\'m in love!! I got this in turquoise for my birthday from my father-in-law (he is the best).. I loved my old one but this was a upgrade for me and I\'m over the moon with this one!! It works great and looks amazing!! Just had to get new cups since this one is smart and reads the lids, but hey it\'s worth it and totally amazing!! Also I enjoy the \"smaller\" size, it don\'t take up as much room as the last one.. I\'m being spoiled being able to pick the size of drink!! Oh and btw this so pretty!! It even tells me to enjoy!! I can\'t be more happy about this!!'),
(4101, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-16', 'Five Stars this is a top notch high End toaster'),
(4102, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-12', 'Great delivery! Buttons, and wires works well. NO damage. Great delivery!'),
(4103, 12, 1, 2, '2016-09-02', 'Product Does Not Function I just connected this product and the toaster does not work.  The bread lever will not engage and so the unit will not turn on.  Unfortunately, it is difficult for me to get to a post office to return items, so I will just buy something different.'),
(4104, 7, 3, 5, '2015-10-08', 'My husband and I have used HB\'s The Scoop for years because we\'re very particular about our coffee, no flavored, no instant, etc. As our favorite blend became available in Kcups, we wished we could have both single cup ground and kcups. We bought this about two months ago, for our son in Canada, to replace the labor intensive coffee press. I was so impressed with the ground coffee result and the kcup, we bought one at home. It is a perfect little machine. We\'re loving the simplicity, easy clean-up, kcups for tea, and, most of all, excellent coffee any time of day, in a matter of minutes. Most of it is plastic, but it\'s high quality, no taste transfer, and all the removable parts are top shelf dishwasher safe. Kudos, Hamilton Beach!'),
(4105, 2, 1, 1, '2015-11-13', 'Due to poor temperature function I bought this item back in Feb 2015. Preset temperatures are NOT accurate. I think the actual temperature is much lower. Due to poor temperature function, I stop using it. Waste money.'),
(4106, 4, 1, 5, '2016-05-23', 'WOW!  JUST WHAT WE WANTED! What a find!  The cabinet profile is terrific and hard to find!  Having dial settings vs. digital is what we wanted.  SIze adds a lot of versatility to more frequent use.  Toaster feature is awesome. I looked for something like this several years ago and gave up; just cleaned the old one and kept using.  Very happy with this purchase and the associated service. Highly recommend this!'),
(4107, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-25', 'Works good. Bought for my son. Works good.'),
(4108, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-20', 'Works just fine So far this is a very good coffee maker. Works good, easy to use and easy to figure everything out. looks good as well.'),
(4109, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-18', 'Easy to use & perfect if you just want a cup! I have never owned a single cup brew system until this one, so I don\'t have anything to compare it to except our full pot Cusinart.  It was super-simple to set up.  From the time I opened the box until I had my first cup brewed was probably 10 minutes.  It brews \"oilier\" coffee than our Cusinart, and perhaps that\'s a good thing.  We were on vacation in Seattle and took a coffee tour and it was discussed how you can see the oils from the coffee bean at the surface of some coffees. I would be very interested in trying some flavored coffee in this brewer, since that\'s what I\'m used to drinking.  It came with some regular coffee blends - like dark roast or breakfast blend.  I\'d also like to try the hot chocolate and other specialty drinks. I\'m not sure it brews the actual amount you ask it to.  When I ask for 10 ounces, it seems like a very small amount, but I\'d have to measure to be certain.  I wish you could have it fill a travel mug without having to run it for 10 ounces and again for 6 or whatever.  You end up with watered down coffee or using 2 K-cups. I did have a problem with it one of the first days I used it.  It basically wouldn\'t drain the water from the Kcup, so when I opened the top, there was a huge mess of coffee water & grounds that I had to clean up.  I also had to run a hot water cycle to clean out the cup area so I wouldn\'t end up with a mouthful of grounds like I did that morning.  However, this seems to have been a fluke and it\'s been working fine ever since! Overall I\'d recommend this brewer for it\'s ease of use and for someone like myself who rarely drinks more than a cup or two of coffee per day.  The touch-screen feature makes it feel fancy and it has a sleek overall design. I received this product free for testing.'),
(4110, 5, 1, 3, '2015-12-21', 'Not very long lasting. Nice coffee pot, but it only lasted two years.  For the money and the ratings I expected more time than that. Now I have to buy another one and I don\'t think I will buy this one again.'),
(4111, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-21', 'Five Stars This replaces a 10 yr old one  great value.'),
(4112, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Absolutely in love!!! Thank you Keurig for the free pods for this review. I do wanna say that I absolutely adore my Keurig. I get so excited to make a cup of coffee. I have it in \"sandy pearl\" and it\'s such a gorgeous unique color and also it is not too big. It\'s just the perfect size and looks amazing in my counter. Coffee tastes amazing and I\'m so happy I have it just in time for fall to enjoy pumpkin spice. I would recommend this Keurig to everyone.'),
(4113, 9, 1, 4, '2016-03-10', 'Ridiculously short power cord I love the older model of this coffee maker but the cord on this new model is absurdly short! You can\'t use it without an extension cord..disappointed in Cuisinart.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(4114, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', '... meaning to purchase one for awhile now and so glad that I was able to get my hands on ... I was meaning to purchase one for awhile now and so glad that I was able to get my hands on one now! This is such a convenient machine, especially for my husband and I who can get by sharing a cup of coffee a day. We definitely don\'t need a whole pot of coffee and this allows us to easily make just a cup whenever we want without excess.  I love that it brews so quickly and is available in multiple sizes suited to your needs (4,6,8, 10) and it\'s nice to have the option of getting carafe for it if we decide we want to be able to brew a larger amount. It\'s also nice to have the \"strong\" option for brewing and I really love that I can now make a variety of hot beverages, including tea in this machine and use the \"hot water\" option for other hot water needs! I do wish that it had the capability to brew a little hotter but for the convenience and all the other benefits it comes with, I don\'t mind that too much. Some people are unhappy that it rejects K-cups from other companies but being new to the Keurig that doesn\'t bother me right now and after looking into it, it seems there\'s easy ways to get around this. I received this product free for testing - BUT this is my honest opinion! :)'),
(4115, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-12', 'And the coffee tastes amazing! When I first recieved it I was worried ... I recieved my brewer for my birthday about a month ago. I use it almost every day. I am very please with the quality and ease of use. And the coffee tastes amazing! When I first recieved it I was worried a travel mug would not fit but the bottom drip tray slides out easily so that my travel cup will fit. Great product that I highly recommend. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4116, 2, 1, 3, '2015-05-29', 'Very basic Toaster Oven Wanted a basic toaster oven but may be too basic since you cannot turn it off once the timer is set.  It has too many adjustments to make to switch from bake to toast too.'),
(4117, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Five Stars Love it!!!'),
(4118, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-27', 'Great Toaster Oven Great toaster oven.  Makes terrific toast!.'),
(4119, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-30', 'Love it! No need to go into details with all of the other reviews to read. This machine makes great coffee, every function is intuitive and simple to operate, the carafe doesn\'t spill a drop of coffee, and the water reservoir and coffee basket insure that making a pot is a no mess proposition. I really like this coffee maker.'),
(4120, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-29', 'Five Stars Great Coffee Maker!'),
(4121, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-04', 'Works great and I love the price Works great and I love the price. Sometimes smells when i use hold down the button too long. Almost like i\'m frying the motor.'),
(4122, 10, 1, 2, '2016-01-27', 'Two Stars There is a burning smell when I am using it....'),
(4123, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-03', 'Pretty simple specification to meet The coffee is definitely made hot enough to properly extract all the flavor from the beans.  Does not take a large amount of beans to make a full pot of coffee.  I bought this specific model because it does not have a carafe (pot) and it has a timer.  These are glass and tend to break in my household.  Pretty simple specification to meet. As far as making coffee, cleaning and overall operation, I am almost completely satisfied.  Easy to fill and start coffee, all the parts come out for easy cleaning and the machine makes a hot pot of coffee pretty quickly (about 7-8 minutes).  The overflow catch under the spout catches not only coffee drips from the spout but any overfill from making coffee.  This really only happens when you put too many grounds in and if you open the lid when its hot, the condensation will drip to the catch.  My only issues with operation are the filter in the water and the gauge.  The filter isn\'t placed low enough where it actually filters any water and the gauge doesn\'t actually really drop until the third cup.  Not a big deal and not bad enough to drop my review from five stars.  It holds four cups of coffee and my water is plenty filtered already. The permanent filter would be better if it were a cone, but the spray function is one of the best I have seen and provides plenty of coverage to thoroughly soak the grounds.  The unit is not a thermal unit, is does have a hot plate.  I go through coffee fast enough where this does not matter, but your coffee will be burnt after an hour. Pros: Easy to use and clean Makes great coffee without a ton of beans Makes a quick pot of coffee Timer is excellent 1-4 cup option for better coffee Looks great on your counter Cons Gauge is useless Hotplate vs thermal Water filter in holding tank is also useless Overall, this coffee pot is perfect for my wife and I.  We do not make top of the line, specialty coffee but also don\'t just go for the cheapest option.'),
(4124, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-04', 'Five Stars Gets the job done'),
(4125, 12, 1, 5, '2016-03-22', 'just the perfect size for two people just the perfect size for two people.  small oven but just right for heating up or cooking smaller meals.  I love the fact that you don\'t need two appliances on your countertop.'),
(4126, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-15', 'Five Stars Works great'),
(4127, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-27', 'Five Stars We love the new keruig. It\'s awesome. U make just what u need and it\'s quick and easy.'),
(4128, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-03', 'Leaking corrected by cleaning This is a great coffee as long as it doesn\'t leak, and you may be able to correct that by cleaning.  The area that seals the coffee in the top can become coated with a  layer of residue caused by the coffee to the point that it will not longer seal properly.  The DCC-3000 has a control button labeled \"Clean\".  Follow the instruction for cleaning as I did and your leaking may be corrected as mine did.  I had large black flakes come during my cleaning and the leak stopped.  I originally blamed this on the quality of the product until I tried this.  Don\'t make the same  mistake I did, CLEAN CLEAN CLEAN!!!!!!!'),
(4129, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-22', 'Fire hazard! MIne developed the same warping and splitting in the heating element that others have reported.  This is a SERIOUS problem, a fire waiting to happen.  A small spot began to glow on the heating element, then became brighter, grew larger until the entire bottom rod curved into an arc.  How ignorant of me for not taking action sooner!  Fortunately, I became of aware of the danger before a fire happened.  Have now unplugged it and filed a report with the US  Consumer Product Safety Commission. Cuisinart! Are you listening?'),
(4130, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'but I\'ve started lining it with foil each use anyway to avoid washing it multiple times a day and it works great. Very happy wit we ditched our microwave and got this for reheating things. the finish on the tray included wore a bit after accidentally being bleached, but I\'ve started lining it with foil each use anyway to avoid washing it multiple times a day and it works great. Very happy with this.'),
(4131, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-11', 'I really like it - much I really like it - much, much better than our previous coffee maker (a Cuisinart - it leaked like a sieve).  I really like how the water tank can be removed for filling at the sink - it\'s very simple to operate.  My only complaint is, there is no chime or ding when the brewing process is complete - very good coffee maker.'),
(4132, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-06', 'Love this coffee maker! Love this coffee maker! Particularly like the smaller cup settings.'),
(4133, 2, 1, 3, '2015-02-27', 'This is a nice oven for the price This is a nice oven for the price.  My main disappointment is that it does not toast evenly. The back section gets very dark before the front section is even toasted.  The settings also seem a little complicated.  I like the idea of a crumb tray that makes it much easier to clean.'),
(4134, 7, 3, 2, '2016-12-30', 'Well it works for a guick cup of coffee. Size is perfect as is the color I chose. Far less expensive than the original K-cup coffee makers especially this size. You have to put water in tank for the amount your mug holds. K-cups are ripped into and sometimes some grounds can be in your drink. If your mug isn\'t directly under dispenser there will be splatter.'),
(4135, 11, 1, 3, '2014-08-21', 'Three Stars thought it would be bigger'),
(4136, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-26', 'Impressive My family  needed a toaster oven for the longest & the Hamilton Beach 22708 Toastation mini oven was the Perfect Christmas gift! It toasted our food nice, hot & crispy & I am surprised how fast it was done. Most people around me did not know that a 2 in 1 pop up toaster /oven exist! This will definitely impress your friends & family. Most people complain their toasters can\'t fit bagels but I\'m impress this one can. Great Product!'),
(4137, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-04', 'It\'s OK Works as advertised. A tight fit for bagels and you have to guess which side toasts the cut side.'),
(4138, 4, 1, 2, '2015-08-06', 'Timer design flaw This toaster has a design flaw that\'s madding and when I tried to alert the company to the issue the representative couldn\'t get me off the phone fast enough.  We had a previous model of this toaster, but needed to replace it after one of the heating rods seemed to split open. Since we had liked that toaster, as well as all our other Cuisinart products, we ordered this newer version. Our household wakes up at different times for work, so its important to try and be as quiet as possible.  The timer for the toast setting on this unite has a flaw -- it doesn\'t reset itself after each use if stopped before beeping.  For example: if you set the timer to medium, but you turn off the toaster before the *5* high pitch beeps go off, the next person who uses the toast function will have the timer and the toaster turn itself off too early.  That\'s because the unit is completing the remaining time for the last person.  The only way to prevent the timer from beeping (5 times) and the toaster turning itself off is to unplug the unit after each use of the toast function.  Actually I also unplug it before making toast just in case the last person forgot.  Hopefully this explanation makes sense. I called this problem into the company right after getting the toaster since this had not been an issue with the previous Cuisinart unit.  But it wouldn\'t be a surprise if future units have the same issue because the representative I talked with claimed to not know if this was a problem just with my toaster or it it was a problem for the model.  They were far from interested in taking any useful information I wanted to give so this issue could be fixed in the future. I thought we could just \'deal with this\' toaster until it breaks, but each time I make toast, I\'m hating it.'),
(4139, 4, 1, 3, '2015-01-04', 'Lower Element Issue on two TOB-40 ovens I have owned 2 of these toasters, I love the Cuisinart. But after about 18 months one of the lower elements started to split and eventually a small flame appeared there. I assumed I had a lemon and so bought another. Lo and behold the same thing is happening to my current oven after about 18 months, one of the lower elements has warped and now touches the bottom of the oven and makes the removal of the crumb try virtually impossible. After reading reviews I am guessing that a replacement oven would also have this problem. so sad as i really like the controls on this oven, it doesn\'t have the awkward timer that most toaster ovens have. I would give it 5 stars for use but 1 for durability.'),
(4140, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-14', 'A bit small but serves the purpose Serves the purpose well in baking and broiling. I wish the baking trays were a bit larger'),
(4141, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-29', 'Four Stars easy to use and makes a good cup of coffee'),
(4142, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-22', 'easy to use Bought this for the RV.  Lightweight and compact, easy to use.'),
(4143, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-01', 'Four Stars Excellent product for the price!'),
(4144, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-10', 'Four Stars Pretty good product for its price. I use it daily to make shakes and it comes out good.'),
