(4146, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-04', 'I love this pot I love this pot....not fancy, easy to use, very fast to brew, and the marker for water faces front so it\'s easy to read.  Too soon to tell if it will be durable, but if it is, we will really LOVE it!'),
(4147, 2, 1, 3, '2016-05-13', 'Using 4-slice toaster oven... So So! Not as I expected....'),
(4148, 12, 1, 4, '2015-05-14', 'Great toaster oven Great toaster oven, nice looking and even toasting small interior space though, but does not take up A lot of counter space easy to keep clean too!'),
(4149, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-19', 'Best toaster!!! This is the second (exactly the same) toaster I have ordered. The only reason I ordered a new one is because after some time, they start to look a little brown and crusty, as all toasters do, and I just wanted a new fresh one. I LOVE this toaster! Go with the older model though... I hear the newer one has smaller slots on top and don\'t really fit bagels/large toast well. Get the one with the black front. The best!!! It\'s also the perfect size to stay on your countertop.'),
(4150, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'What a great machine: I love the different cup sizes I ... I purchased the Keurig 200 to replace my old Keurig .  What a great machine:  I love the different cup sizes I can select and the sleek, stylist look.  My wife made a great choice.  We got our moneys worth.  Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(4151, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-12', 'best coffee machine I have ever owned best coffee machine I have ever owned! love  not having a glass carafe to deal with, the light is a great feature so you know when the cup is full and also love the gauge of how much is left!'),
(4152, 6, 1, 3, '2017-01-04', 'Three Stars Has worked great since I got it. Sometimes gives off a slight plastic smell when it is toasting something.'),
(4153, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-01', 'Works great so far for all my cooking Works great so far for all my cooking.  I use it more often than my oven it gets hot faster due to the small size.'),
(4154, 11, 1, 5, '2015-06-24', 'Five Stars love this oven.  I cook and reheat pizza in this little gadget'),
(4155, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-22', 'Good toaster Love the cool part.'),
(4156, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-19', 'Little Toaster Oven that Performs Big. Basic, simple and performs well for a very low price.  Perfect to reheat pizza pieces, French fries, and toast bread. Save electricity for baking small quantities of finger foods.'),
(4157, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-05', 'Five Stars Looks great'),
(4158, 6, 1, 3, '2015-06-05', 'Ok for toasting. You have to rotate for an ... Ok for toasting.  You have to rotate for an even toast if using a single slice.  Too many of the crumbs don\'t end up in the tray so you have to shake it upside down to clean.'),
(4159, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-09', 'AWESOME!! I LOVE< LOVE< LOVE this!!!  I use it as much as I can.  I no longer need to heat the oven up to cook for 2.  I love all the settings, and it also has a timer function.  This is awesome!'),
(4160, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-19', '... present for my son and according to him it\'s great. That\'s was a Christmas present for my son and according to him it\'s great.'),
(4161, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-22', 'I especially like filling the water container directly from the faucet What can you say?  A simple but effective means of brewing coffee. I especially like filling the water container directly from the faucet.'),
(4162, 10, 1, 2, '2015-06-01', 'What is the point. I was SO excited for this product. I went to make my first smoothie in it today, and it couldn\'t even handle sliced frozen banana with yogurt. I guess the little motor and blade might work well to mix together already slushy ingredients, but if you\'re going to call yourself a blender, you should be able to blend ingredients like frozen fruit chunks.'),
(4163, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-25', 'have done several 12\" pizzas and its worked wonderfully. Definitely better than a regular toaster oven Heat up in minutes, have done several 12\" pizzas and its worked wonderfully.  Definitely better than a regular toaster oven, or heating up the house with a stove.'),
(4164, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Great Improvement I purchased the Keurig K250 2.0 in white about a week ago. I had a Vue Brewer which was mysteriously discontinued a year after I purchased.  I found the Vue cups were getting harder and harder to find so I bought this one.  Overall it\'s a great improvement over the previous Keurig Brewers.  It\'s pretty quiet. The touch screen and the cup size options are nice.  It heats up quickly and  it\'s very convenient for someone who needs a cut of coffee as they\'re running out the door for work.  I\'m happy that I can use older Vue cups I have left over from my previous brewer.  The biggest downside is that you can only use Keurig brand cups.  Also, I have some older K cups that will not work....The new brewers have a sensor to read the new K-cup foil covering.  Overall I\'m satisfied and purchased at a great price.  Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(4165, 9, 1, 4, '2016-09-18', 'It makes a great cup of coffee and stays warm without burning I\'ve been using this for about a month.  It makes a great cup of coffee and stays warm without burning.  I\'m questioning if already the coffee is not as hot as it was brand new.  I still enjoy the ease of operation and quality of coffee.'),
(4166, 6, 1, 1, '2016-06-23', 'I have had this toaster for 4 months. The ... I have had this toaster for 4 months.  The lever won\'t stay down in position for toasting the bread.  Very disappointing for a Cuisinart mid priced item!  I have been cheated!!!'),
(4167, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-04', 'Five Stars Love this coffee pot. Isn\'t nothing I don\'t love about it.  Recommend it highly.'),
(4168, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-07', 'Five Stars Love it. Use it every night.'),
(4169, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-09', 'Great toaster! Love this toaster!  Works perfectly and the bread slots are not tiny which is good!'),
(4170, 4, 1, 4, '2016-12-08', 'Package came on time and was easy to install Package came on time and was easy to install. Not sure about registration process. The toaster itself works great. This is my second one as the first one died after a few years of usage.'),
(4171, 8, 1, 4, '2014-01-24', 'Dips when pouring BUT It serves the purpose for now. I had it on hand for a while  just in case I needed it. The only thing I hate about it is that when you pour the coffee it drips all over the place. It makes a good cup of coffee, and I have always liked Black and Decker products so I just ordered the same 12 cup coffee maker from them that recently broke after several years of use. They are inexpensive and do what every maker does regardless of cost.  Like many others, all I want from the coffee maker is hot coffee.  I don\'t need all of the other gizmos that they charge for.'),
(4172, 5, 1, 1, '2016-12-09', 'Very defective. Have to return it. I am ... Very defective. Have to return it. I am hoping the replacement lives up to the reviews I read about it.'),
(4173, 9, 1, 1, '2015-04-05', 'Poor Design results in Inconveniences The coffee maker\'s basket lacks the depth needed to keep grounds from getting into the coffee reservoir.  As a result, the coffee maker needs to be throughly cleaned after each use.  Also, due to this design flaw, only 6 to 8 cups of coffee can be made unless an user wants weak coffee.  Further, tall cups and thermoses will not fit on the base plate to pour coffee.  It\'s going back after one week of use.'),
(4174, 10, 1, 2, '2016-02-05', 'Buy this if you want to watch your smoothie go up in smoke!!! I liked the concept of this little blender but it didn\'t live up to my expectations. I bought this to use to make smoothies in my dorm room without having to worry about storing a huge blender and could easily make one serving size to take to class with me. I found that when using frozen fruits it just took too long to blend it down to a good consistency especially since after a minute or two the motor would start to smoke and give off a nasty burning smell. This began to happen with VERY LITTLE use, practically new. I also found it very difficult to get the lid on and off and the contents of the smoothie would leak out the top making a mess. Overall not happy with this purchase.'),
(4175, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-15', 'This is the BEST coffee machine that I\'ve EVER bought in my 76 years. This is the BEST coffee machine that I\'ve EVER bought in my 76 years, and I\'ve bought dozens, i.e., I can\'t say enough good things about it. MY WIFE AND I LOVE IT! BTW This specific one is one that I bought for a relative.'),
(4176, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-11', 'Five Stars Good!'),
(4177, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-28', 'and the bottom wheels make it easy to slide out and back in This coffeemaker works perfectly for my kitchen.  I have low-hanging cabinets and my old Keurig coffeemaker wasn\'t able to slide underneath.  I replaced the Keurig with this Hamilton Beach maker and it fits perfectly under the cabinets, and the bottom wheels make it easy to slide out and back in.  I also love the detachable water reservoir.  So much easier to fill.  Makes a great cup of coffee, and you can adjust the heating plate temp and the brew setting from light to bold.  Now I look forward to waking up to freshly brewed coffee waiting for me.  And the price was just right.'),
(4178, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-21', 'Five Stars Very good!'),
(4179, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-28', 'top notch pot Excellent product. Thanks.'),
(4180, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-21', 'I really like this pot I really like this pot. I like how the condensation drips into the tray. The coffee is hot, especially the first cups. It doesn\'t burn the coffee & i have it set to stay on for 3 hours. I had a hamilton beach before and I hated that thing with a passion, coffee burned after 1 hour and the condensation was a nightmare to get out! I have had this for a couple of months now and I have been happy with it! My mom even bought one after using this one.'),
(4181, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-20', 'Sturdy, reliable, they love it Requested gift, already given. They love it. It cooks 4 of anything at one time. Good for a growing family. I was concerned about the quality of a Cuisinart product. In my opinion they ruined the original Cuisinart mixer, but this has been a good buy.'),
(4182, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Well satisfaction is guaranteed by my Amazon Great toaster'),
(4183, 8, 1, 4, '2014-03-15', 'good enough I have a problem with drinking whatever coffee there is.  If I am going to wind up drinking the whole pot I figured a good solution was to get a smaller pot.  Nothing fancy about this little guy.  Which means fewer things to break!  Ever have a pot with an alarm you can\'t turn off?  I have.  Damn thing chirping at me before I have had enough coffee too cope was awful.  Only complaint I could make is you have to remember to shut it off....oh no.'),
(4184, 2, 1, 3, '2016-09-27', 'The Good and The Bad Good points on this appliance: looks really nice. It matches our SS appliances so it looks ok sitting out on the counter; Has lots of options/settings for various types of heating/toasting; the inside crumb tray makes it very easy to clean & keeps the crumbs off the counter. The not-so-good is what others have noted about unpredictable toasting. I\'ve learned to be Very conservative in setting the temp --- use the lowest until you know how it comes out, and Never set it and leave it. Keep an eye on it. Last- lots of heating/cooking options means lots of control settings. Who wants to reset 3-4 different controls - which aren\'t that easy to read - just to do 1 simple item?.'),
(4185, 9, 1, 5, '2016-06-14', 'Good purchase! Great coffee maker. We love it and use it everyday!!'),
(4186, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-28', 'Fresh coffee on tap! We first used this when we went on vacation and it was in the kitchenette. Fell in love right away with the simplicity of getting coffee on tap. Ordered this when we got home. Setting the timer gives us freshly brewed coffee in the morning or whenever. We also have a Keurig but this is so much cheaper in the long run. Very satisfied!'),
(4187, 6, 1, 4, '2014-12-31', 'Four Stars It is an excellent value, but when toasting one slice, the sides of the bread are toasted unevenly.'),
(4188, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-07', 'Good buy, good design I have been using this for several months now, and I have to say it is very well designed. I go through a coffee pot about every two years, and if this one lasts longer than that it will be an additional plus. All of the other little irritating features of most coffee pots have been eliminated from this design and it seems some one put a lot of thought into it. I would buy this coffee maker again at this point, but it has to make it at least two years. I will update as far as its longevity when the time comes.'),
(4189, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-27', 'Great automatic coffee maker It\'s very easy to set for the next morning and makes the coffee relatively quickly.  Doesn\'t leak or get dirty very easily.  Clean it with vinegar once in a while to keep it functioning properly.'),
(4190, 11, 1, 4, '2015-10-19', 'Four Stars It will quickly burn the toast so be careful.'),
(4191, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-25', 'Fantastic Value Great toaster oven.  Even greater value.  The size is great.  The versatility is great.  Highly recommend.'),
(4192, 4, 1, 4, '2015-11-15', 'Like it, dont love it... Under engineered when it comes to turning off the \"oven mode\" .  Controls easy to read as long as you don\'t need readers.'),
(4193, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-04', 'Funky timer knob and instructions Compact, attractive toaster oven heats up quickly.  However, the first time I ordered this, the bottom timer knob broke with only a day or two of light use.  The replacement seems to be working, but the instructions claim that the timer knob must first be turned \"past 10 minutes\", and then back to a shorter time if you want to, for example, toast something.  It is very difficult to turn the knob backwards and especially not easy for an elderly person.  Also, in fact, it does not appear that you actually need to turn the knob past 10 minutes in the first place.  So the instructions are confusing.'),
(4194, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-11', 'And how my Dunkin\' Donuts coffee tastes like it comes from the store I recently used this coffee maker at a Diamond Resort. I had never seen it before. I purchased it two weeks ago. And how my Dunkin\' Donuts coffee tastes like it comes from the store. The coffee keeps good and hot. Not like my last coffee maker luke warm. Best coffee maker I have ever used.'),
(4195, 11, 1, 5, '2014-12-23', 'works great for toast and foods like any oven it takes ... works great for toast and foods like any oven it takes a few times to find the right setting but checking during operation keeps from burning anything'),
(4196, 1, 1, 1, '2015-06-20', 'Error message when dispensing hot water after making coffee This machine dispenses a maximum volume of 10oz.  I have a larger mug so I set the Keurig at 10oz with the \"strong flavor\" mode on.  Then I dispense some additional hot water to bring it up to volume.  Unfortunately, I always get an error message when I try to use the hot water function.  I suspect that when I brew a cup of coffee the steam generated blocks some sensor so I get an error message.  After I wait a few minutes, the error message disappears and I can use the hot water function.'),
(4197, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-20', 'This was a Christmas gift for my elderly mother. This was a Christmas gift for my elderly mother. She absolutely loves the toaster oven & it\'s simplicity to use & care for'),
(4198, 4, 1, 4, '2017-01-19', 'Four Stars Simple to use. Lettering on dials need to be a little more visible.'),
(4199, 12, 1, 4, '2014-10-12', 'just not as sturdy as I was It works well, just not as sturdy as I was hoping'),
(4200, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-12', 'Had to return due to defective product Had to return due to a defect but Amazon\'s return policy is excellent. Before you throw away the packing materials, get some kind of bread, bagel, whatever and try out all the settings. Mine wouldn\'t work with the bagel setting, and one of the other settings didn\'t work for the first few tries but for some reason it kicked in eventually.'),
(4201, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Love our second Keurig This is the second Keurig that we have purchased.  Love the flexibility of making, coffee, tea or hot chocolate.  Had problems with our keurig cups, but the company replaced them.  Love the color.'),
(4202, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-09', 'Nice toaster oven I really like this toaster oven, works well and easy to clean. It is smaller and I like that for my counter space. I can fit 4 pieces of bread inside perfectly.'),
(4203, 5, 1, 1, '2015-08-13', 'but I\'m not happy that I only got a month of use out ... I received this on 7/6/15, and today (8/13/15) it simply stopped working; I pressed the on button and it did nothing, except heat up the hot plate--coffee didn\'t brew. The window to return it ended seven days ago. I know coffee makers aren\'t the most reliable appliances, but I\'m not happy that I only got a month of use out of it.'),
(4204, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Great for common areas Wonderful............Use it all the time in a common area with college age.  No clean up and low maintenance so it\'s perfect. \" Thank you Keurig for the free pods for reviewing my Brewing System. I have received compensation for writing this review, but would have said the same thing if I didn\'t receive anything.\"'),
(4205, 5, 1, 4, '2016-06-21', 'GREAT except for one flaw... so close to a 5 but a couple issues.  first, the good stuff.  well designed, easy to use, so cost effective.  the most annoying aspect of a coffee maker has been addressed with the removable reservoir.  no more pouring water all over the counter, into the coffee basket, etc.  it\'s not a bad looking device for the price, and the cup capacity is great for the size. the bad part...it arrived broken twice.  the control panel at the top is anchored with some screws or something, and either during shipping or during the mfr. process, the posts that anchor the display \"frame\" break off.  when the first one arrived damaged, i sent it back for another thinking it was just bad luck.  when the second one arrived with the SAME damaged part, i determined it was a bad design flaw. however, i was so eager to keep it i just decided to live with it and glue it back into place.  it\'s a $38 coffee pot.  expectations can\'t be too high. hopefully other brands will take cues from this model and start to make more user-friendly machines that don\'t look like and SUV.'),
(4206, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-28', 'Five Stars Toasts beautifully. Sleek styling. Will see how it lasts!'),
(4207, 3, 1, 4, '2016-10-24', 'but so far so good. Just got it, but so far so good.'),
(4208, 4, 1, 4, '2015-09-07', 'okay for two years Had this toaster oven about three years. Worked fine during the first two of those years - but then the oven door hinge began to malfunction, such that it was often hard to fully open or close without pulling / pushing hard. Finally, a few days ago while I was pulling to open the door, the glass shattered.Toaster oven kaput. Update September 17, 2015:  I called Cuisinart when I realized that my 3 year warranty was still in place - after I reported the problem with the door, they promptly sent me a new toaster oven. Very impressive!'),
(4209, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-10', 'It\'s a good buy Drip coffee makers, regardless of brand or cost,  seem to crap out after a year and a half or two.  I\'ve gone through 2 Cuisinarts and 2 Frigidare units, and in frustration, bought a percolator - which may outlive all of us,  but is a messy thing to have to confront every morning.  I like to arrive downstairs and be greeted by a full, hot pot of coffee every morning, and the only way that\'s going to happen is to have a drip unit.   I figured that there was no point in overspending on one,  and went about researching lower cost units.  Mr. Coffee seems to lead the pack on these, loved by Consumer Reports, but reviews complain of a water filter that must be positioned ever-so-delicately in the unit every time you\'re making a pot.  The Hamilton Beach had no such complaints, and cost-wise is right where I\'m OK if the unit turns out to be disposable in 18 months.   I\'m very pleased with this coffee maker.  The water reservoir pops right out for easy filling (don\'t have to try and pour into it while ducking under the wall cabinets), the basket for your grounds pivots out forward of the unit (no way for grounds to end up in the reservoir, if you\'re being uncoordinated), and programming it was simple and intuitive.  It takes about 10 minutes to make a full pot, and the coffee is as hot and strong as what my Cuisinarts produced.   Coming out of the box,  the unit feels pretty lightweight, but not flimsy. Maybe it\'ll die in 18 months, who knows? For now, it works well and is easy to use, and it\'s far less messy than that percolator.  At this price, I\'d buy another just to keep in reserve,  but we\'ll wait and see. **Update 3/30/15 - Arrived this morning to a coffeemaker that had crapped out. No heat, no coffee, just a light on.  So....15 months of daily use,  kind of what I expected. It was good while it lasted.'),
(4210, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-02', 'A Tea Drinker\'s 1st Coffee Maker I\'m a tea drinker that has gone over to the dark side. This is my 1st coffee maker, ever. I got it for the 1-4 cup feature but I\'m not exactly sure if that makes a difference or if it actually does anything. I don\'t know if the water gets warmer faster. The directors also don\'t make that clear either. I also got it because it is programmable and I LOVE that feature. I\'m asleep in the morning so the thought of trying to mess with making coffee at 5 am is not appealing. I set it  the night before and by the time I am ready to leave my house the coffee is ready and waiting for me. On the weekend, when I make more than 4 cups of coffee, the coffee stays nice and hot for 2-3 hours. I haven\'t really used it pass 3 hours. I\'ve read other reviews where people complain about a plastic taste. I \'cleaned\' it with Apple Cider Vinegar, which required like 3 rinses but I never had an issue with a plastic taste or smell.'),
(4211, 7, 3, 5, '2014-12-31', 'Love this as I\'m a single person living alone. Sometimes in afternoon I wanted just a cup of coffee after having tea in a.m. This works so easily. Of course, you have to use good coffee. I\'ve used Seattle\'s Best and Kona. So tasty!'),
(4212, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-08', 'Perfect for College Dorm Purchased this three months ago for my daughter living in a college dorm.  She loves it and still uses it every day.  Perfect for smoothies.'),
(4213, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-28', 'so good. Easy to use and very user friendly So far, so good. Easy to use and very user friendly.'),
(4214, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Makes a great cup of coffee! The water filter is a great idea for those who don\'t have conditioned water. It may take a minute for the water to heat but that precise temperature is what it takes to get that great taste. I have no need for the carafe so that is not an issue for me. I have some of the old k cup pods that will not fit this machine. Not so good. Another issue is that there aren\'t many coffee choices for those of us who can only drink decaf. Too bad.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4215, 5, 1, 1, '2014-11-10', 'My wife doesn\'t like it -I gave it to her as a gift-she ... My wife doesn\'t like it -I gave it to her as a gift-she wants a different one-so sending it back & will order the one,she wants.thanks Amazon !! My wife decided to keep it. Next one she\'ll pick it-and we will buy it from Amazon !!! -we love Amazon'),
(4216, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Great toaster oven! So happy with this toaster over!  It looks great and works great with an unbeatable price!'),
(4217, 4, 1, 5, '2016-08-27', 'Just what the cook wanted Just what I expected.'),
(4218, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-28', 'I love this coffee maker I love this coffee maker.  This is the 2nd one of the same model.  The first one lasted about 18 months, not as long as I would have hoped but I guess things aren\'t made like they use to be.  The water container is separate and removable which is my favorite feature so I\'m not spilling water everywhere when filling it.  All other features are great.  I\'m the only coffee drinker in the house and use it once a day.'),
(4219, 11, 1, 4, '2015-02-06', 'Great product Easy use & clean. Versital & reliable. Use it everyday. Small & sleek. Great value! Cons: Make a bit noise at the beginning then quite after 2 months use. Hopefully it\'s normal.'),
(4220, 2, 1, 1, '2016-05-18', 'This oven needs to be removed from Amazon. This toaster oven clearly has a design defect& should be removed from your shelves...  I had the fire department @ my home just trying to make my morning toast...  With in minutes of putting the bread in, the thing was up in flames...  I tried to use it two more times but I had to stand in front of it because it did not go off on its own...  Thank goodness I had kept my old toaster oven & I\'ve gone back to using it.  Sadly, I threw away the boxes, so it would be difficult to return...  I\'m just grateful that it\'s over...  By the way, this is the very first time that I have ever had a problem with an Amazon product...'),
(4221, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-10', 'Excellent toaster for the price Excellent toaster for the price. I love the pop-up feature...no more burns from english muffins. A sleek surface, easy to clean.'),
(4222, 6, 1, 4, '2015-05-31', 'Happy with this toaster I had no idea buying a new toaster would be so difficult... I read so many product descriptions and reviews before getting this.  I am very happy with this toaster. My needs: four slices and bagel-friendly. It is handier than I realized having two settings/controls. The extra nudge-it-up-higher feature is way nicer than digging out short toast. My one and only complaint is that the darkness control knobs spin too easily and don\'t stay on their settings, forcing me to remember which settings my husband and I each prefer and reset each time.'),
(4223, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-01', 'works pretty, pretty, pretty good it works. on button turns it on and starts brewing the pouring from the pot is a little iffy, it\'ll spill a little usually but not a huge deal.'),
(4224, 4, 1, 5, '2016-06-06', 'Five Stars Love it. use it everyday to make toast and bake.'),
(4225, 5, 1, 4, '2016-01-30', 'Four Stars Replacement carafes are outrageously expensive. Otherwise I would rate this five stars.'),
(4226, 4, 1, 4, '2015-07-20', 'Good Solid Toaster Oven Solid toaster and heats food well.  Haven\'t cooked with it yet.  The door with the hooked tray requires getting used to but is OK.  Had a previous model of this and worked well for a long time.  Wished it was all stainless like the previous model.'),
(4227, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'This toaster is awesome. No need to pay more This toaster is awesome. No need to pay more. It gets hot but cools down quickly after each use. Do not sit anything on top if it or around it. Keep out of children\'s reach. A great purchase. I don\'t know how we lived without it.'),
(4228, 7, 3, 2, '2016-10-13', 'We returned it, we bought it for the price to take on trips with us. We both use k-cups. I use 8 o\'clock and my husband uses McAfee. With the 8 o\'clock it worked good, the water was hot and it was fairly easy to use, but with McAfee cups it destroyed them. The cups were a little different on the bottom of the cup, so the cut thing didn\'t puncture them right.'),
(4229, 7, 3, 4, '2015-05-08', 'I like the coffee maker, I have had it for over four months. The only exception to the four stars is that just recently the Flexbrew has decided to make only a half of cup of coffee and stopping. I then press the start button to finish the second half of coffee. It to me is a mild irritation.'),
(4230, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-26', 'Still worked great! I was able to used this thing for so long and until now, it still worked great!.'),
(4231, 7, 3, 4, '2014-08-11', 'Love the hot fresh cup of coffee this small compact machine brews. My only complaint is how slowly it brews'),
(4232, 9, 1, 1, '2016-04-19', 'Ridiculous Power Cord The description you read from Cuisinart fails to tell you the power cord is about a total 6 inches long.  Obviously this will not reach a kitchen counter wall plug.  Now I have to order a 1 foot extension cord and wait another 3 days before I can use it. I would not mind the short power cord, but I do mind that they ignore telling you that it is that short.....never have seen such a short cord on any kitchen appliance.  WEIRD !'),
(4233, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-18', 'Good for one person use Good for one person use. Very easy to clean. Used the same product for a while and just bought another one. The only downside is that you need to push the button all the time until the smoothie is ready to drink.'),
(4234, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-21', 'I saw horrible reviews for so many coffee makers online I bought this for my elderly father in October of 2013.  His previous two coffee makers broke within a few months.  He wanted a light up display for a programable coffee maker. Their kitchen is small so it needed to be compact as well.  I saw horrible reviews for so many coffee makers online.  Very few had a light up display and they were gigantic or not programable.  He has had this coffee maker for over a year now and has had no problems with it.  It is simple to program, easy to fill with water and the part that holds the coffee grounds is easy to open, close and remove the filter holder.  The wording on the buttons has faded a bit.  That is a minor detail for him since he knows which button to hit every night.'),
(4235, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Five Stars Bought if as a gift for my daughter !!  We already have one and it\'s terrific'),
(4236, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'Good Toaster Looks nice on the counter with my white appliances.  Toasts evenly!   Cuisinart did not disappoint!'),
(4237, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-23', 'Great toaster! Great toaster. It performs well on bagels, English muffins, toast and not much else. I can\'t imagine anyone would need to toast anything else but I have never tried. It toasts evenly and works consistently as expected. If it lasts for a long time I will update the review. So far it has been great and a good value for the price. Frozen toasting feature is a plus as well.'),
(4238, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-31', 'Great, product Great, product, great packaging, exactly as described. Works super well. Doesn\'t stain too too easily if you wash it after every use! I have been very happy with my purchase and the product is easily worth more than it costs!.'),
(4239, 2, 1, 2, '2015-03-28', 'Not great Not very impressed with this toaster oven.  It either burns my toast or doesn\'t toast it at all.'),
(4240, 6, 1, 1, '2015-07-27', 'Broke after 1 year Broke after 1 year. The right hand two slots don\'t work.'),
(4241, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-15', 'Stops Turning On This machine just stopped turning on.  I liked it fine but I will never trust another Hamilton Beach product again.  I paid too much for using it only for three months or so.  STAY AWAY.'),
(4242, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-13', 'Five Stars Great little toaster'),
(4243, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-07', 'Five Stars nice'),
(4244, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-29', 'Great for bread Got this toaster to replace an older model we had that would not shut off.  Toaster works well, one star off for its small size.  Great for bread, not so great for anything requiring a pan.'),
(4245, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-18', 'like 2 days Ordered a red one to brighten things up.  Delivery was very quick, like 2 days.  Works well, takes up a little less space than our Elite.  The 3 cup size choice is nice but I wish it would stay at what ever is selected rather than revert back to 8 oz each time.  Also Kuerig offers some specials on coffee which makes them a very good deal.  Coffee is jsut hot enough, brewing very easy and short preheat time.'),
(4246, 5, 1, 2, '2015-12-05', 'Poor reservoir design I have had this coffee maker for about 6 months and I am getting ready to replace it.  The removable water reservoir is very easily dislodged from the body of the machine, resulting in no or very little coffee ever making it into the carafe.  I had this happen this morning and I checked the fit between the reservoir and machine before I turned it on.  It has happened enough times for me to lose trust in the product.'),
(4247, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-28', 'Five Stars I found the lowest price here http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004JMZGM2?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creativeASIN=B004JMZGM2&linkCode=xm2&tag=dailybrainfre-20'),
(4248, 11, 1, 4, '2016-09-23', 'the toaster oven I had mysteriously started working again. the toaster oven I had mysteriously started working again.  So I gave this one to my son for his RV.'),
(4249, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-30', 'at half price, it would be overcharged. toasts on one side only, then uneven, at that ! Must be a refurbished ?'),
(4250, 4, 1, 2, '2016-02-11', 'I think most of the electric toasters have cheapened the ... I think most of the electric toasters have cheapened the quality & durability of their parts. We haven\'t even used our Cuisinart and when we opened the oven door for the first time, it would not close tightly. We packed it up and sent it back. Very disappointing.'),
(4251, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-10', 'Dripless Drip Coffee - Finally! After all the Mr. Coffee, Cuisine Art, Kitchen Aid and other drip coffee makers I\'ve had all these years, this one finally is one worth living with. It\'s swing away filter holder and removal water reservoir allows me to reload it without actually having to move the unit. And, best of all this thing does NOT drip when removing the filter or when you pull out the decanter. If you are tired of cleaning the burner every time you get a cup of coffee, or change the filter...this is the one! Controls are all easy to use and the whole unit is smaller than average. Very happy with this purchase about 3 months ago!'),
(4252, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'We Love it!! I really like this model Keurig. The auto brew feature is a life saver for my husband in the morning. We have owned other Keurigs in the past, but the new updated features on this model are exactly what we needed. Auto brew, options for brew size, carafe brew, plus you get to pick your own wall paper on the display screen. Who wouldn\'t love it?'),
(4253, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-09', 'Coffee Addict LOVE! LOVE! LOVE! Great product for the price point... removable water tank, GENIUS! Also, the different brew settings has been quite a nice feature.'),
(4254, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-29', 'Great coffee maker! I bought this coffee maker because the one I had didn\'t have an auto-off.  While I\'m not a big coffee drinker I entertain a lot and wanted a decent coffee maker for my guests. I love the easy cleaning and filling of this unit.  The styling is great and it makes a good cup of coffee.'),
(4255, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-24', 'Hamilton Beach coffeemaker This coffeemaker is fine, except for two inconveniences. The reservoir is in the back which requires turning the coffeemaker each time it is filled. The pot itself is 12 cup capacity, but if filled to 12 cups it is difficult to pour without spilling. I have restricted my coffee making to 10 cups. Otherwise the coffee is fine and it keeps coffee warm.'),
(4256, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-09', 'Five Stars Your price is much affordable compare to other brands.'),
(4257, 9, 1, 1, '2016-08-25', 'It\'s too bad because I really like the system This is my my third coffee maker of this type and brand. The first lasted about 3 years. The second, 1 year. The dispenser tab would not close all the way and all the coffee would leak out all over the counters and cabinet. Thought it was a one time flaw, but the new one is doing the same thing. It\'s too bad because I really like the system. Will have to go back to the old stay by coffee pot.'),
(4258, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-20', 'Everything i wanted Luv it'),
(4259, 12, 1, 5, '2014-07-08', 'Wonderful, multipurpose gadget for our office Wonderful, multipurpose gadget for our office.  We can make a lot of our lunches in the office and save money.  It looks nice, works well, and clean up is easy.'),
(4260, 6, 1, 1, '2015-09-23', 'A toaster can\'t possibly work worse than this So this toaster...ugh. Immediately when I purchased it I realized there was no setting in between not toasted and burned. I can\'t even understand how a piece of bread can burn so quickly! And somehow it would be practically \"untoasted\" on the opposite. If you think the explanation behind this is that the toaster was set on bagel, but it wasn\'t. Oh, and the thing smokes, too. I guess that something that can burn bread in a matter of seconds would do this. It also shouldn\'t have surprised me that the side with the \"working\" heating coils and back quickly became too hot to touch. Oh well!'),
(4261, 8, 1, 3, '2016-03-04', 'Still spills coffee. This coffee pot makes good coffee. But it still spills the brewed coffee. I had hoped the straighter sides would eliminate this problem (previous coffeemaker was a Mr. Coffee) but it didn\'t. Will have to find another brand to buy.'),
(4262, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-07', 'Five Stars We love it hubby drinks a lot of coffee and this one is prefect for him.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(4263, 4, 1, 3, '2015-11-16', 'Only 2 years and I have to replace it now!!!  Arrgghhhh!!! This oven worked fine and I loved it till recently.  The bottom 2 burners in the oven have stopped working, rendering it nearly useless.  I have had this oven exactly 2 years now!!  Already I have to replace it!!  Arrghhhh!!!'),
(4264, 5, 1, 1, '2015-11-28', 'Lasted only 7 months Broke after 7 months of use. Won\'t turn on. I have tried in at least 5 outlets in different parts of the house.'),
(4265, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-01', 'You\'ll like this little coffeemaker. Great for college students, or single people. Quick and easy.'),
(4266, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-28', 'Five Stars love it works great'),
(4267, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-11', 'Five Stars works great'),
(4268, 10, 1, 3, '2016-04-07', 'Three Stars Great for the price but cheaply made.'),
(4269, 6, 1, 1, '2014-12-28', 'BIg disappointment Really, Cuisinart? I ordered this toaster because I\'ve always thought the brand to be high quality. I was wrong. How hard can it be to make a toaster that toasts a slice of bread evenly?? The only way I can use this without one side getting burned is on the lightest setting, which is too light. Such a disappointment. A cheapo toaster at Target or Wal-Mart works better than this!'),
(4270, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-18', 'Five Stars It\'s perfect to my family'),
(4271, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-04', 'It\'s all Good This product was delivered in good condition, and works great for my purpose.'),
(4272, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-27', 'Five Stars love the different settings!'),
(4273, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-08', 'Cuisinart makes very good coffee makers Cuisinart makes very good coffee makers. I don\'t think this on demand coffee maker keeps the coffee as hot as the first one they made. Still great, a repeat buyer of Cuisinart.'),
(4274, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Great coffee maker I guess I am not as high maintenance as some who have written reviews.  I really like my Keurig`I find it to be fast taste is good and easy to operate.  I have recommended it to some of my friends and they liked it too.  My only concern,I drink Decafe and there is not much selection in flavored coffee.  I am hoping soon that will change.'),
(4275, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-27', 'Great present I bought this toaster oven as a present for my parents for Christmas.  They used to only use a toaster in their home.  I, however, already owned a toaster oven (different brand), and I liked my toaster oven a lot better than their toaster.  I decided to buy this brand and model for them due to its popularity and the reviews it got on Amazon. My parents are very pleased with this toaster oven, and they say they have permanently put their old toaster away,'),
(4276, 3, 1, 4, '2015-11-05', 'Great Toaster Oven.......Slow to Heat Up It performs all the functions it claims to do.  Love the size and ability to get to all the areas that need to be cleaned.  My only beef would be that it takes a while to get it done.  The instruction sheet says you don\'t have to preheat, but I almost always hit the toaster button while I\'m prepping so it\'s nice and hot before I put in my food.'),
(4277, 12, 1, 1, '2014-07-09', '2 both died within short period of time This is a huge disappointment as our second toastation has just broken after only one month.  We bought the first one in January and it died completely one week after the period when I could return it for a refund.  However I had loved it so much I ordered another thinking it was just a bad one.  ONE month later this too has broken.  The oven works but not the toaster.  I loved its size and color but thought the toaster only so so.  With thin sliced bread it allowed the bread to curl up, but since I mainly used it for bagels it was ok.  Now that is gone for the second time and I am giving up on it completely.'),
(4278, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Love it, but it is plastic easy use, easy clean.  The only thing I don\'t love is that it\'s plastic so can\'t use it for anything hot...and I\'m afraid of BPA/other harmful chemicals in plastics.'),
(4279, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-02', 'Five Stars Useful!'),
(4280, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-09', 'Miracle in a cup :-) Awesome Blender. I\'ve been using it for over a year. To ensure longevity, clean after each use. Also, the button says \"pulse\" so try not to keep the motor running for more than 10 seconds at any given time. Blend, then stop for about 5, blend again. This has helped me so far with no issues.'),
(4281, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-15', 'Great toaster with oven feature We toast more than use the oven. Love this because it works like a regular toaster but can use the I\'ve. For larger breads. Oven is not big enough for much else.'),
(4282, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Five Stars It\'s a great oven toaster! I love the overall quality. perfect fo heavy duty use.'),
(4283, 9, 1, 4, '2015-01-03', 'Good.. But can\'t adjust Good..But can\'t adjust strength'),
(4284, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-01', 'Love it! Heats so quickly!  Love it!.'),
(4285, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-28', '... got it for me as a present and I love it. My wife got it for me as a present and I love it.'),
(4286, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-09', 'Lighter than the old one, hope it lasts 10 years like the old one did. This is the lightest toaster oven I have ever owned.  It is very close in size to my old B&D toaster that finally died Saturday night.  This model is quite basic with a basic price of $23.99 for Prime members.  I ordered it Saturday night and it arrived Tuesday afternoon. The pan included is small and almost unusable.  I have an array of pans that fit in this unit so that is not a problem for me.  The colour scheme is silver and black and not as easy to read the dials as my old white B&D toaster oven.  The operation is straightforward and includes a 30 minute max timer.  The removable crumb tray is an upgrade over previous models.  For several years I used the B&D spacemaker toaster ovens.  They stopped making them, but have a new model available for $100.  I decided to go with this unit as the price was easier to live with.  At this point I would recommend this toaster oven and at this price, I am considering buying one as a hot spare.'),
(4287, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-03', 'great toaster toaster is nice looking and works great.'),
(4288, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Loved this keurig Loved this keurig! It fulfills my coffee-loving needs and even lets me make hot coco and tea :) It isn\'t big and bulky, and it\'s super cute! This is a must buy!! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4289, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-28', 'Four Stars Good product'),
(4290, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Hot hot hot Love my new coffee maker!  It makes my coffee very hot, just the way I like it!'),
(4291, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-30', 'Great cup of coffee all the time. My husband couldn\'t get a good pot of coffee with our old coffee maker. So I bought him a 550 he liked it so much we purchased a K250 for work so he can have a great cup of coffee all of the time. Draw back, K cups are not cheap, but you also don\'t waist a pot of coffee. You also need to keep the needles clean my newest one comes with a needle cleaner my older one did not. I also fill the water tank with a small pitcher so I\'m not moving the water reservoir to much. Just need to clean up the occasional water spill.'),
(4292, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'I love it. I am not a coffee person I love it. I am not a coffee person. But I love having coffee twice a day with my keurig. I love how easy and convenient it is. I need to get my dad one.'),
(4293, 6, 1, 1, '2015-01-06', '... had to return this toaster--thank you Amazon for the easy return and credit-- The center heating element burned the ... I had to return this toaster--thank you Amazon for the easy return and credit-- The center heating element burned the toast at any setting, while the outside element toasted fine. Uneven and not good. Would not recommend at all.'),
(4294, 6, 1, 4, '2016-02-01', 'She said she liked it. This was a gift. She said she liked it.'),
(4295, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-22', 'This thing just works - great for under cabinet We have gone through numerous coffeemakers.  I grind beans every night and use the timer to have the coffee ready early AM.  Reasons I like this one - Easy to fill the removeable reservoir and so far it hasn\'t leaked.  The swing-out filter basket makes loading coffee very easy when the unit is under a cabinet.  The display is quite bright and easy to read - something my old eyes appreciate.  Very good for the money, hope it holds up.'),
(4296, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-15', 'The coffee on demand is the best of all Beyond loving all of the features. The coffee on demand is the best of all!.'),
(4297, 11, 1, 4, '2014-02-09', 'Nice small toaster We got this toaster because it\'s small and we are able to put away in the cabniet. It looks ok and works. It makes toast (up to 4 slices) beside that it\'s a toaster'),
(4298, 12, 1, 4, '2015-12-21', 'Good product Doesn\'t exactly toast evenly, but it\'s super convenient and does a pretty decent job'),
(4299, 7, 3, 1, '2014-01-23', 'This machine worked for 1 week and began to run more slowly each day. Today\'s cup of coffee took more than 10 minutes to brew; and, in the meantime it sprinkled coffee all over the counter, steamed crazily and gave me 3/4 of a cup at the end. Not good quality. I wish I had kept the receipt because I would really like to return it and take my $50 and put it toward a Keurig instead. :('),
(4300, 5, 1, 1, '2017-01-10', 'Design flaw is annoying. We returned the first one and received very ... Design flaw is annoying.  We returned the first one and received very quickly and easily a replacement.  Unfortunately after the 2nd pot of coffee the same design flaw appeared....the front cover plate over the digital dial just snapped off after closing the coffee basket(original equipment).  I would not recommend this product.'),
(4301, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-24', 'BUYER BEWARE OF EXPLODING GLASS Cuisinart TOB-40 Custom Classic Toaster Oven DANGER!!!! I had mine for 15 months until today.  The door had been sticking some and tonight when my son opened it, the door came off in his hand and the glass shattered.  It literally exploded into hundreds of pieces all over the kitchen: the floor, the countertop, the stove and the sink. We are fortunate that he was the one it happened to.  He was not hurt but rather shaken by this event.  I don\'t know if I would have been so lucky. It has taken him over two hours to clean up this mess. I am surprised that Cuisinart had such a poor design with this unit.  This could actually have hurt someone very badly or perhaps killed them. Look at customer images and you will see two images of what this unit looked like after its assault on us. DO NOT BUY THIS UNIT AND PERHAPS NOTHING BY CUISINART AGAIN.  NOT TO BE EXPECTED FROM SUCH ASN A-1 COMPANY.'),
(4302, 8, 1, 2, '2016-03-20', '... but I do not think that the appliance brews good coffee. The coffee maker brews too rapidly - ... I got what I ordered but I do not think that the appliance brews good coffee.The coffee maker brews too rapidly - so the coffee just flows through and is weak and tasteless. I have inserted paper filters in the mesh cup and I am using more coffee and it helps. I wish I had selected a different coffeemaker.'),
(4303, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-24', 'Hooked already, I hope this expensive new habit doesn\'t cost too much! Hooked already, I hope this expensive new habit doesn\'t cost too much ;).'),
(4304, 10, 1, 2, '2016-02-11', 'virtually useless for blending liquids as the top is junk Not sure why this product has so many positive reviews. I tried using this expressly to prepare bulletproof coffee in the morning, I use a regular blender for anything that necessitates actual grinding/chopping/blending. The coffee literally explodes through the top of this thing, virtually useless for blending liquids as the top is junk. After attempting to make a couple batches of coffee, I gave up and bought the Oster BLSTPB-WOR blender, basically same price but it\'s a \"closed system\" so there is no opportunity for the coffee to explode out of any seams.  Not sure if this review is helpful as it only evaluates the blender in one context (blending of liquids) but if you are purchasing it for that purpose, take a pass.'),
(4305, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Five Stars Super Value'),
(4306, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-27', 'Great Toaster Oven! I am happy with this toaster oven.  It is a nice size; not too big, not too small.  Works great!'),
(4307, 3, 1, 2, '2014-02-21', 'awkward controls, not the \"toaster oven\" i expected if you are looking for a simple toaster oven i would stay away from this unit. Controls are funky, and the oven stays on even after being turned off some times. Can\'t seem to get toast right in this machine, as it seems to dry out and burn it if I don\'t watch what i\'m cooking the entire time. I have tried manipulating the timer, and seem to dry out my bread opposed to toasting it. on the flip side, I make great homemade bread crumbs in this oven.'),
(4308, 6, 1, 3, '2015-04-29', 'Works like a normal toaster Nothing special. Works like a normal toaster. It\'s been a few months of normal usage and the markings on the front are coming off when cleaned with water and soft tissue. I am planning to take a picture of the markings before all of them are gone'),
(4309, 4, 1, 1, '2015-09-21', 'Do not buy this toaster oven Do not purchase this toaster oven. If you do, save your receipt.  We received ours as a wedding gift 4 years ago. The heating element on the bottom is now busted open, posing a fire hazard (as described in many other reviews here). I contacted Cuisinart and they said if I couldn\'t provide a proof of purchase then there was nothing they could do. Sad that a company as reputable as Cuisinart doesn\'t stand by the safety of their products.  Although it is out of it\'s 3 year warranty period, one would\'ve hoped that they would care about consumer safety and satisfaction anyway. They don\'t.'),
(4310, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-03', 'Works like it\'s supposed to Works like it\'s supposed to! Easily programmable. And the wheels on the bottom make it so nice & easy to move around when filling the reservoir or getting coffee. We\'re very happy with this coffee maker!'),
(4311, 5, 1, 1, '2015-02-18', 'Stopped working after 9 months. Warranty requires that you ... Stopped working after 9 months. Warranty requires that you pay for shipping the defective unit back to the manufacturer as well as pay for the new unit to be shipped to you.'),
(4312, 3, 1, 5, '2014-05-18', 'no better toaster oven We had a similar model but after many years the handle broke off and we couldn\'t get a replacement. Unfortunately this happened around the holidays and I couldn\'t get a similar toaster.  We purchased 2 other toasters that we thought would be similar but either looked terrible or just didn\'t have the ease of function.  Finally, decided to order this one, but given backlog had to wait almost 2 months.  Finally, the toaster arrived and it was well worth the wait and trouble.  There is nothing else I would want a toaster oven to be.  Easy to use, looks great and is very flexible in terms of what you want to get done!!  You will not be sorry!'),
(4313, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-22', 'Four Stars So far this coffee pot is working great.'),
(4314, 4, 1, 4, '2015-07-11', 'All You Need In A Toaster Oven I have liked this toaster oven.  It toasts evenly and has been great for cooking or reheating items.  Since it is only my husband and I it is nice to be able to use this for a meal vs. turning on the large oven and using all that electricity.  It has a nice crumb tray that slides out for easy cleaning.  It seems as though the rack inside should hook up to the door somehow so that it would slide out when you open it but I haven\'t figured that out yet.  It would probably be a good idea to get the manual out and read it!  The price was very fair for this product'),
(4315, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-19', '4 star rating! Like the fact  it makes 4,6 8 or 10 ounce cups.  Also can make a stronger cup.  Don\'t have to wait for the water to heat, just lift handle & put back down, ready to brew.  Had an older brewer that had to be turned on & wait to heat up.  this one is a lot better. Draw back is this one takes only Keurig  cups, old one would take other brands.  Did have one brand of hot chocolate that worked. I\'d give this a 4  star * will buy one as a gift for family.'),
(4316, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-06', 'Nice little toaster oven If you are in need of a small toaster oven, this one is perfect. Very basic design and simple to use. The timer is a nice feature.'),
(4317, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-21', 'Finally a Keeper This the seventh toaster I have purchased two different brands were bought at Target, one at Walmart, four from Amazon, This was the only keeper.Its hard to find a good toaster.  I went by the Amazon reviews with all my purchases, and I only purchased 4 Star + toasters.  They all had the same problem, no matter what the cost, the elements would not heat correctly, in turn you might only have toast on one side, or half the slice would be toasted.  I really think its the luck of the draw with these toasters, you might order this one and have a problem with it, but I finally got one that works. The second best (that I\'m keeping as a back up) was a sale toaster that I paid $6.82 for.'),
(4318, 8, 1, 5, '2014-06-22', 'For Grandmom We purchased this for my grandmother who did not want a Keuring.  She just wanted a coffee maker for herself, since she is the only person that would be drinking coffee.  She can easily operate the coffeemaker and there is just enough coffee for herself.'),
(4319, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-01', 'great This thing is a beast. The bottles can be a pain to clean, but the blender itself is amazing. Just be sure to not put frozens right up against the blade, and it\'ll chew through anything you put in it.'),
(4320, 10, 1, 3, '2015-12-27', 'Three Stars Even with light use it didn\'t last very long.'),
(4321, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-22', 'Pros: It turns. It can mix very small ... Pros: It turns. It can mix very small mild amounts Size is tiny. Maybe be able to handle a small amount of pre-chipped ice. Packaging and shipping A+. Cons: 3 Ice cubes too much to crush. Rotation speed very slow. Motor sounds strained even with small amounts.'),
(4322, 10, 1, 3, '2015-01-28', 'Not that great It wouldn\'t blend when I put a lot of stuff in it at once and the quality isn\'t that great but I\'m just gonna use it.'),
(4323, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-10', 'Great coffee maker, simple, with options. Probably one of the best coffee makers I\'ve ever bought.  Just enough options, without needing an IT education to run it.  I like the coffee strength choices, and that I can keep the coffee warm, but not piping hot.  Now, if I could just find out where to buy a back-up carafe, for when I inevitably drop or bust the current one, I\'d be a happy man.'),
(4324, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-01', 'worked fine until hit by lightning was a gift , worked fine until hit by lightning :-(.'),
(4325, 6, 1, 2, '2014-09-22', 'Very disappointed. I couldn\'t believe it didn\'t toast my bread evenly, on one side it was dark and the other light.  Very disappointed.'),
(4326, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-20', 'Great item, fast delivery Great item,fast delivery!'),
(4327, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-19', 'Solid single cup coffee brewer Convenient machine for personal use. The only thing is I wish you can customize the water amount when you just want hot water, but solid machine. Nice and small, looks cool, works well. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(4328, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-05', 'looks good and takes up very little space on the counter The only con I have about this product is that it does not have a timer to set for a specified amount of time.  (the toasting section will beep).  It works very well, looks good and takes up very little space on the counter.'),
(4329, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-14', 'Very Good Brewer The model I received says K250 even though the review goes to the K200.  I don\'t know what if any differences there are between the two.  This brewer makes excellent cups of coffee and tea and is incredibly convenient with the individual k-cups.  It seems you have to add a lot of water just to make a single cup but other than that this seems to be a well maVery Goodde and easy to use way to brew great coffee.'),
(4330, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-28', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(4331, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Reliable, Good Coffee, Has Everything You Need This is just an excellent simple coffee maker. The removable water reservoir is a time- and mess-saver. This is one of the few carafes that does not spill when poured. There is not a confusing abundance of controls, but you can adjust the warming heat and program brewing in advance--the only two features i ever use. We had a prior model hamilton beach and really appreciated the removable water reservoir (why doesn\'t everyone do this?). When it broke down after five years, ended up buying an expensive ($150) Capresso machine with thermos carafe. The coffee was no better, and we did not like the thermos without a warming plate--thought it would be good so that coffee does not get burnt warming, but the coffee was never really hot. After a month, put it back in the box and bought this model....much happier!'),
(4332, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-14', 'Five Stars very happy with this product.'),
(4333, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-14', 'good value Looks nice, works well. Bought so I can use when just wanting to heat without turning on oven.'),
(4334, 4, 1, 1, '2015-08-31', 'Not Quality NO, this did not meet my needs.  It did not make good toast.  I could not get it to function it the way I had expected.  Therefore I sent it back!!!!'),
(4335, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-19', 'Does its job I\'ve had it for about a month and it works as expected.'),
(4336, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-16', 'Best coffee maker ever We love your Keurig 2.o.  It is the best coffee maker we have ever had.  It is easy to use and makes the best coffee ever.  No more messy coffee filters needed and we can have a cup of coffee in an instant.  Love it.'),
(4337, 3, 1, 4, '2016-07-14', 'so good. I have used the bake and broil features ... So far, so good.  I have used the bake and broil features and the bagel feature.  The toaster oven heats up without generating much heat in the room.  The only reason I didn\'t rate this item a \'5\' is that I found the instructions concerning starting the time and temperature a little confusing.'),
(4338, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Five Stars Blends well'),
(4339, 11, 1, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Five Stars works well and easy to clean.'),
(4340, 8, 1, 4, '2015-07-04', 'I would have given it five stars, but the ... I would have given it five stars, but the fact that they saved money by not having the little toggle clip at the bottom to keep it from leaking coffee onto the hot plate when you remove the carafe takes away one star. Other than that, it does exactly what it is supposed to do: makes coffee.'),
(4341, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-22', 'Four Stars Just so-so. It works not well and use inconvinient.'),
(4342, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-02', 'Does the Job! Love it, doesn\'t take up much room on my countertop.  Only wish it had a little more power, but all in all no complaints.'),
(4343, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-19', 'Five Stars I like the look and very easy to fill'),
(4344, 12, 1, 2, '2016-11-09', 'Two Stars Good idea but way to small!.'),
(4345, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-09', 'Great little unit that does what it is supposed to ... Great little unit that does what it is supposed to do: toast bread, bagels, muffins and rewarm small items little a slice of pizza. You cannot expect to use it to prepare a gourmet meal. If you\'re looking for miracles, look elsewhere and be prepared to spend much much more. This is my third unit, I donated the older one, still perfectly functioning, to a thrift store. For a little over 20 bucks you certainly cannot do better. I am very happy with it. I highly recommend it.'),
(4346, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-15', 'Four Stars This was for a friend and she says that she likes it'),
(4347, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-16', 'Very practical and easy to use Very practical and easy to use.  It is easy to clean via the slide out drawer.  The tray is easy to slide in and out and the settings make your toasted item just the way you like.  The volume is impressive as well for a small oven.'),
(4348, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-17', 'So perfect My old toaster oven broke a few weeks ago. (The oven worked, but it stopped toasting.) After looking at a lot of options on Amazon, I decided on this one and have been using it for about a week. It works amazingly. I love that you just spin a dial and then it counts down. (My sister has a digital one where you have to punch in temperatures and it is really tedious. This is an area in life where analog is better, in my opinion.) I\'ve gotten great toasted bagels from it, and it heated up some chicken earlier today perfectly. It also looks sleek and modern. I don\'t have any large things to put in it. If you do, I would probably look for a different model. It\'s fine for me, but I could see some people thinking it was on the small side.'),
(4349, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-17', 'Burnt toast anyone? I don\'t know if I\'m just unlucky but this toaster was a complete lemon since day one. You never knew haw it was going to toast whatever the setting. Like a goof I kept messing  around with it and went beyond Amazons 30 day return policy. Now I\'m waiting to see how the manufacturer will stand behind his product. We didn\'t use the toaster daily so I\'d act on the problem and return it sooner. It\'s one of those things like it\'s never a problem until the next time you wanted to toast something, I had this approximately two months and used it maybe a dozen or so times. I finally quit procrastinating and just bought another one locally. This one is working OK. I read the Amazon reviews and I know the toaster got a lot of 5 stars. Like I said maybe I just got the lemon. So---here\'s my one star. I just think the quality control should be up to the manufacturer not the customer,'),
(4350, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-20', 'Great coffee maker Great coffee maker. Better than my old Bunn.'),
(4351, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Love the Keurig and how easy it is to use I switched to this after having the single serve Keurig for years.  Love the Keurig  and how easy it is to use.'),
(4352, 12, 1, 3, '2014-01-26', 'Cute Toaster Very compact and good looking toaster. One complaint is that it will only turn off if power supply is unplugged. Otherwise very pleased.'),
(4353, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-26', 'Easy to cook and clean up best toaster made. I have 2'),
(4354, 7, 3, 1, '2015-01-02', 'I bought this because I want to move AWAY from K-cups but, in the meantime, I have some \"soft-bottomed\" (filter bottom, not plastic) K Cups that work perfectly in my current Keurig machine that I need to finish off. Well, they DON\'T work in this coffeemaker. In addition, using the ground coffee filter produced only very very weak coffee. This was returned to the store.'),
(4355, 5, 1, 4, '2015-10-13', 'Almost perfect I don\'t expect my coffee maker to grind the perfect coffee every morning but do expect to make a decent pot of coffee.  I was rather intrigued when I saw this coffee maker had a removable water tank.  Cleaning the water tank had been a pain in the past but this removable tank makes it so much easier. This coffee maker is pretty smart. If the water tank is not latched on properly, it won\'t brew.  When it happened first, I thought it was broken already.  But I soon noticed that the top of the water tank was not quite leveled.  All I had to do was push the tank and restart the machine. This coffee maker has different options for the temperature and the strength of your coffee.  Though it has a \"1 - 4 Cups\" brew setting, I recommend using \"Bold\" if you prefer stronger and richer flavor regardless of the amount of the coffee. The only problem was the glass carafe.  The lid didn\'t snap on tightly so every time I pour the last couple of cups, it would swing open and the hot steam would come out.  When I used it for the first time, I had the high temperature setting.  So it almost burned my hand.  I lowered the temperature and held the lid with a pot holder since. However, its carafe was flimsy. One morning when I tried to clean the carafe, I tapped it on my Quartz countertop accidentally.  Not hard at all.  But it was enough to break the carafe.  I searched and searched for the replacement.  There were replacements on Amazon, but the reviews weren\'t great.  When I went on to Hamilton Beach website, the carafes were out of stock (surprise!).  So I decided to try Cuisinart carafe instead.  I had used one of their coffee makers before and their carafe never broke.  Thankfully it fits and has been working great.  Cuisinart updated their lid to snap on instead of swing open.  So it stays tightly even when I pour my last cup.  The picture shown here is with the Cuisinart carafe. And here is the link to the Cuisinart carafe sale. http://smile.amazon.com/gp/product/B0000CFNE3?psc=1&redirect=true&ref_=oh_aui_detailpage_o05_s00 If Hamilton Beach made their carafes sturdier like Cusinart, I would give it a 5-star.'),
(4356, 1, 1, 5, '2016-07-24', 'Five Stars i love it!.'),
(4357, 5, 1, 3, '2016-08-20', 'Good coffee, but..... I bought this machine a few days ago because of several features that I liked....the removeable water resevoir, the swing out filter basket and overall good reviews.  It does make good coffee and the features are still great....but...in swinging out the filter basket sometimes brushes against the plate covering the control panel and the last time it did this that plate fell offf.  After investigation I discovered that the screws holding the plate on had broken out, so now the plate keeps falling off when the filter swings out.  Its a minor thing that I can probably fix, but indicates shoddy quality and I suspect this machine probably won\'t last very long.  Still,  at its marked down price, its not a bad purchase and it does make good coffee.'),
(4358, 6, 1, 1, '2015-01-26', 'Terrible toaster I have tried various settings and both sides of the toaster with the same results.  One side of the bread is toasted nicely and the other side is burned.  I do not recommend this product.'),
(4359, 1, 1, 3, '2016-08-24', 'too basic for price. For the price I paid (at kohls)  I\'m disappointed how basic this is. I would\'ve been better off buying a $50 regular coffee maker. I can\'t set the temp, I don\'t like my drinks the temp of lava. It doesn\'t have a clock or a way to program it to turn on before I wake up. I seriously should\'ve done more research. Should\'ve just bought a coffee pot. I regret this purchase.'),
(4360, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-15', 'Good product and price This replaced a 21 year old Black and Decker Toaster Oven. So far, we are happy with the new one. The only minor issue is that the timer knob is very \"stiff\" and hard to set at the exact position we want for toast. But that does seem to be loosening up with use.'),
(4361, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-25', 'Great little big oven! This toaster oven has saved our day(s)!  We are RV\'ers and our RV does not have an oven.  This one fits perfect in a small space but is still big enough to bake what we need.  Perfect for us.  It is high quality craftsmanship.  The only difficulty we have with it is the buttons have the controls written in black on the silver buttons and is very hard to see unless you have good light in the room.  Other than that...perfect!'),
(4362, 7, 3, 5, '2016-03-20', 'We had an older single serve Hamilton Beach coffeemaker which lasted 4 years with daily usage. We are very pleased with this replacement purchase and its versatility. I highly recommend this coffeemaker'),
(4363, 3, 1, 5, '2014-04-25', 'Great oven Great functionality for the price! I couldn\'t be happier!  It is roomy, has great features, and overall we are very satisfied with our purchase.'),
(4364, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-02', 'Does the job at a great price. The removable water reservoir is great Does the job at a great price.  The removable water reservoir is great! Would recommend to anyone at this price point.'),
(4365, 10, 1, 1, '2015-04-02', 'No good for making Bulletproof Coffees! I bought this for making bulletproof coffee. Within a few months, the plastic mixing jar got a bunch of cracks in it and leaked all over the sink. I tossed it in the recycle and bought a larger unit ( Hamilton Beach model 58148A Power Elite Multifunction) with a glass mixing jar. Now I am happy. I could probably make two or three Bulletproof coffees at once with the big oversized glass jar.and it doesn\'t leak at all.'),
(4366, 4, 1, 4, '2016-11-05', 'Quality counts! Excellent for baking, but disappointed that the top gets so hot.'),
(4367, 12, 1, 2, '2015-11-15', 'It looks good, but not a great TOASTER Toasts uneven. Thin slices get stuck.  I use the OVEN to get the job done.  No problems with the \"oven feature\".  Pretty and easy to clean.'),
(4368, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-12', 'Four Stars Perfect for smoothies and easy to use.'),
(4369, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-16', 'This thing is awesome. I was looking to replace an old coffee ... This thing is awesome. I was looking to replace an old coffee maker. We only use this bigger one for company, so I was looking for something inexpensive. This fit the bill perfectly. It is easy to use. The water tank detaches from the back for easier filling. The coffee goes in the front flip-out door. Easy easy Best part, coffee taste great.'),
(4370, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-19', 'Great for people with limited counter space This is the most convenient toaster oven for me since I primarily use it for toast, and I can pop 2 slices of bread in the top. It\'s a nice-looking machine. The design of this takes less counter space than most toaster ovens, which tend to be wider, but note that this one cannot broil, and the trade-off is a smaller space to cook in. I got this when my old toaster died since it toasts well, and it\'s nice to not have to turn on the oven for simple toast -- I\'ve used it for making bread-pizza, or warming up a slice of cold pizza. This goes up to 450F. I cooked a couple of biscuits in it once and it turned out pretty decent.'),
(4371, 5, 1, 4, '2015-06-30', 'Last one lasted a year and a half.. This is overall a really good coffee maker.  I bought my first one late November 2013.  Unfortunately, after a year and a half it started taking over an hour to make 4 cups.  I followed the cleaning process, however, the heating element became impossibly clogged to the point nothing would pass through it.  I went so far as to disassemble it and using a variety of tools, tried to scrape, drill, and melt the minerals out.  After hours of effort I gave up.  (decent youtube video on this for the brave and handy)  I used only store-bought spring water in this machine, so I was surprised at the amount of mineral deposits.  I learned a valuable lesson, CLEAN YOUR MACHINE FREQUENTLY with vinegar as instructed.  I\'m hoping this next one will last much longer, and I hope this information will help other lazy people like me who assumed cleaning was optional.'),
(4372, 11, 1, 1, '2014-08-18', 'Used this for less then a month. Toast always ... Used this for less then a month. Toast always burned no matter what setting you put it on. If you didn\'t take it out before the lightest toasting option was done, it was burnt. Today it caught on fire and burst into flames. Luckily I was standing right there and sprayed it with the sink sprayer. I\'ve never been so scared.'),
(4373, 5, 1, 4, '2015-10-19', 'Four Stars Nice coffee maker !!'),
(4374, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'I will say that this unit is the BEST coffee maker that I have owned I ALWAYS read the negative reviews first. ( that\'s just my style ). I am still unsure if this coffee maker will last a long time - the reviews frequently indicated a short lifetime. I will say that this unit is the BEST coffee maker that I have owned. The BEST ! I have had quite a collection of coffee makers over the years Most negative review items are of little actual consequence. Your mileage may vary.  .'),
(4375, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-23', 'we love this one toaster and oven so nice this is ... we love this one toaster and oven so nice this is out second one we love it so much first one lasted a long time with lots of use'),
(4376, 4, 1, 1, '2015-01-04', 'A badly designed product I bought this Toaster Oven yesterday (not on Amazon) and returned it by end of day.  The lowest setting gave me dark toast.  The rack tips down when it is automatically pulled out (causing the contents to slide off, of course).  The toaster does not turn off when the door is opened, which I considered a safety hazard.  It looked like a good product in the store but turned out to be a very disappointing purchase.'),
(4377, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-05', 'Great price for this toaster oven Great price for this toaster oven, Works well and is great for work or home. Would definitely recommend this item'),
(4378, 9, 1, 4, '2015-12-20', 'Four Stars OK'),
(4379, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'This unit is small enough for the counter and great for quick heating This unit is small enough for the counter and great for quick heating. Beats the socks off a microwave.'),
(4380, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-16', 'good for the money I\'ve been using this blender for a few weeks and have not had any issues with it.  My only disappointment is that it\'s not supposed to be used for hot liquids.  I guess I should have read the product description better.  If you fill the container portion too high, the liquid will spill through the slide on the the top lid.  I use a paper towel to cover it whenever I make something 12oz or more to prevent possible spillage.  It does not spill between the reservoir and the cover but through the opening in the cover for pouring.'),
(4381, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-02', 'Best toaster ever Love this toaster!!!!!!!!.'),
(4382, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-22', 'Five Stars Good, simple little coffee pot. Does the job.'),
(4383, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Good Bought it for my son and he really likes it.  Good quality'),
(4384, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'Excellent choice Perfect toaster for the price. Several settings for a wide range of breads, bagels, etc.'),
(4385, 8, 1, 1, '2015-08-24', 'i got black+decker my orderd was black&decker i got black+decker my orderd was black&decker'),
(4386, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-25', 'Thanks it is working out much better than I thought This was not my first choice.  I wanted to purchase a Oster Oven.  It was alittle bit more and digital a more updated model.  But I GOT the B&D so I am content with my new oven.  Thanks it is working out much better than I thought.  It is a bit smaller.  Works for me.  Thank you a happy camper.'),
(4387, 5, 1, 2, '2016-03-30', 'Not as good as reviews. This maker takes a long time to brew and coffee is not very hot.....after having it for 9 months.'),
(4388, 4, 1, 5, '2016-10-12', 'Five Stars Works just like original wit ha few small improvements. Last one lasted 9 years.'),
(4389, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-01', 'The \'\"darling\" of drips! We have been using a Hamilton Beach drip since Hector was a pup.  You can rely on it to make a good cup of coffee - no latte, no white foamy topping - just a darned good cup of \"Joe\".  Love that timer -nothing like waking up and the coffee is waiting.'),
(4390, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-07', 'Great toaster over for a small space. A good quality toaster/oven that fits nicely in a small space.  Both temperature control and timer are quite accurate.  Well made and easy to clean.'),
(4391, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-12', 'Love it! $10 cheaper than Target. Love it!.'),
(4392, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-24', 'Five Stars Great price. works very well. Good purchase!'),
(4393, 6, 1, 1, '2015-12-14', 'Don\'t buy this one..... Lousy toaster that never toasts evenly!'),
(4394, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-24', 'Five Stars Love the pot. good price,.'),
(4395, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Cuisinart compact 4 slice toastter this toaster looks fabulous, takes up limited room for a 4 slicer.  both sides do their own thing.  it makes great toast every time.  I love it.'),
(4396, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-11', 'Really good buy!! Love it. Brews Great and looks Great on my counter. Definitely worth the money!'),
(4397, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-20', 'This is the third one I have bought for other family members who use ours. Great for summer to warm up small items . Great combo of toaster and toaster oven .'),
(4398, 7, 3, 4, '2014-03-07', 'Though it is no comparison to the renowned Keurig brewer, it is good for personal use, easy to take care off.'),
(4399, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Great Purchase for the Price I like to make smoothies in the morning before work and this is a quick and easy way to do it. You do get what you pay for with $15 but I have had it for several months with no problems. I use frozen fruit instead of ice and with quick rests during the pulse it works fine. I do make sure to put the juice (or whatever liquid you are using) in the cup first to make the blending easier. I was hesitant to buy because it was so inexpensive but for $15 if it only lasts me a year I have no problem buying another one. The only thing I have annoying is that it only comes with 1 cup and I can\'t seem to find a way to purchase just a cup.'),
(4400, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-16', 'This is a fantastic coffee maker This is a fantastic coffee maker, we have had it for a few months and have no problems.  It brews a nice, rich pot of coffee with a timer that makes it ready for when we wake up.  Nice features like brewing a bold or light pot make it even better, the pot does not drip.  The reservoir is nicely removable for convenience.  This is a well designed coffee pot.'),
(4401, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-13', 'Poor quality I bought this item in November 2014 and it was dead by June 2015.The lever broke.'),
(4402, 10, 1, 3, '2015-10-28', 'Good for the money. Its a neat little machine but its kinda low on power. I read one description that told of the motor starting to smell after using it too much. That is absolutely true with the one I received. After holding the button down too long, there was definitely a smell coming from it. However, if you\'re a little gentle with it, it works great. And you cant beat the price. If you just want a little low cost, single serve blender, go for this.'),
(4403, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-07', 'Five Stars Love it. Easy to use, I start baking more often now.'),
(4404, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Toastation Sensation! Hamilton Beachs 22703 Ensemble Toastation Toaster Oven is perhaps the most important invention mankind has ever made. I cannot begin to tell you the extent of the toaster and toaster oven related drama I have been living with for the past seventeen years. My daughter is fond of toast, but she is not fond of the toaster. My husband and I would often wake up to screaming to find our daughter curled up behind the refrigerator, sobbing. When we asked her what was wrong, she would whimper and point to the half-burnt, half-limp bread protruding from our toaster. As she became a teenager, we would get in shouting matches over the bagel setting, and I had to drive down to the police station more than once to pick up my daughter after a night of toaster vandalism. My son, on the other hand, adored the toaster. He cried for weeks after our old model bit the dust, and even requested we hold a funeral for our faithful little appliance. Needless to say, when the topic of buying a new toaster oven came up in one of our weekly family meetings, he was devastated. For weeks, my children fought over which new appliance we would add to our home, and there was hardly a moment of the piece. Thats when my husband found the Hamilton Beach 22703 Ensemble Toastation Toaster Over, a miracle device that is both toaster and toaster oven. Since its addition to our home, the fighting and violent outbursts from both of my children have stopped and our home is peaceful once again. I even found that theyve taken to toasting their bread together. I will forever be indebted to Hamilton Beach for making my house a home once again. Oh, and it also toasts sandwiches.'),
(4405, 5, 1, 4, '2014-11-12', 'Probably the best I\'ve owned. I like all aspects of this machine but one. The pour spout is not great. Once you learn it it\'s fine. But the first pour stands a good chance of being a miss. The blue LED read out can be read across the room and is bright enough to serve as a night light. Easy to set up time and ready for operation. The water reservoir is very cool and fits under my refrigerator filtered water tap. One thing...when you are breaking the machine in...do not forget to empty the carafe after the first...second and maybe, third pot of rinse water. Since you do not use the carafe to fill the reservoir it is easy to forget you have a full pot of water. Don\'t ask me how I know this...!'),
(4406, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-24', '77 years old and my daughter and I agree that it\'s the best we have had. The reservoir simply needs emptying before brewing! Bought one at garage sale. (Seller went to single cup machine.)Best Buy ever! All sections are removable for cleaning The coffee is held in a reservoir that keeps it very warm. It did leak one time, but after pushing lever up - no repeat dripping. 77 years old and my daughter and I agree that it\'s the best we have had. ( Our previous purchase of new Cuisineart coffee brewer led to problems w/carafe size changing and impossible to buy carafe. Tried one with metal carafe - big mistake. Coffee never warmed! My son got tired of us having to return products. He bought us a cheap Mr. Coffee! Just got this one by $3 price. lol. I think it would be worth full price!).'),
(4407, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-19', 'Great cup of coffee and easy to fill water First cup of coffee from this coffee pot this morning.  Set it up last night, and woke up to a great pot of coffee.  I love the \"no mess\" water reservoir.  The blue lighted digital clock is very easy to see. Easy fit under my cabinet and the base does not swivel but it is on a base that will turn around easy for access to the reservoir. The front stainless steel is a little thin, but I am glad I spent a little extra money for this coffee pot without spending a fortune.'),
(4408, 11, 1, 4, '2014-07-23', 'Four Stars Excellent toaster/oven similar to the one I a have a home.  Bought this one for my travel trailer.'),
(4409, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Great coffee pot Great coffee pot for my needs. I\'ve been using it for 2 weeks now and I can\'t really say that I have any complaints about it.'),
(4410, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-08', 'Makes good coffee, price is right. 2 weeks in and i really like this coffee maker. Yes it is missing a lot of features that other coffee makers have, but it does what it is supposed to do. It makes good coffee (the water temperature is correct). It is easy to cleanup afterwards. And the price is right. No idea if it will give me years of good service but if it breaks in the future I would be more than willing to replace it with another one.'),
(4411, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-05', 'It serves our needs very good and that is it toasts bread after buying and tossing multiple walmart toasters, we got this one last spring, It serves our needs very good and that is it toasts bread, bagles, and english muffins perfectly'),
(4412, 4, 1, 1, '2015-10-12', 'Very nearly caught our house on fire! We had this toaster oven for about 2 years and I loved everything about it, until it failed catastrophically! I used to it roast some veggies as a side dish for dinner. Removed the food and turned it off. Later that evening, we heard a loud pop noise,but weren\'t sure where it came from, since no one was in the kitchen at the time. We checked around the house and chalked it up to the TV/DVD player which was running (and had coincidentally skipped) at the same time. I just happened to walk through the kitchen on my way to bed later that night and found the toast oven was still on. ...and not just on, on full power and blazing hot even on the outside. Turning the power switch on and off did nothing. It had to be unplugged to shut it off, It had super-heated the cabinet above it and no doubt had I not noticed it, we would have awoken to a smoke alarm and our kitchen engulfed in flames. There should be some kind of safety shut-off or fuse or something to prevent this type of incredibly dangerous failure. I\'m highly disappointed!'),
(4413, 12, 1, 5, '2014-01-19', 'Great toaster We are on our second of these little toaster ovens.  We love that it is a regular toaster and also a toaster oven.  We don\'t use it for any major baking, but for heating/browning things that need to lie flat it is very handy.'),
(4414, 8, 1, 5, '2015-12-05', 'Five Stars Excellent maker and prompt as well.'),
(4415, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Replaced our Keurig Really like this machine. Works well, looks good sitting on the countertop. Nice feature that allows you to brew 1-4 cups.'),
(4416, 6, 1, 4, '2017-01-08', 'Four Stars Pretty content with the product, good if you like more of a crispy piece of toast.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(4417, 5, 1, 1, '2016-08-11', 'Very disappointed with this product Very disappointed with this product.  I do love that it has a removable water reservoir. However, as other reviewers have noted the face plate covering the control buttons fell off within 24 hours of opening the box.  It looks like the plastic on the inside of the cover is broken so it can\'t just be snapped back into place. Hot glue would work I\'m sure but I don\'t really want to keep a brand new product I have to glue together.  Additionally,  this model does not come with a safety feature to prevent brewing if the pot is not where it should be.  I know this because my husband took the pot out during the night in search of coffee, forgot to replace it, and the next morning I woke up to 10 cups of coffee all over everything.  Will be returning this product today and purchasing a different brand.'),
(4418, 6, 1, 4, '2015-09-22', 'nice basic toaster good toaster at a great price.'),
(4419, 6, 1, 3, '2016-07-08', 'Three Stars ok'),
(4420, 5, 1, 2, '2016-11-12', 'I really loved this coffee maker I really loved this coffee maker. I bought it in December 16, 2015 it stopped working October 26. 2016.  It had no power, no lights, nothing.  Tried plugging and unplugging.  Just dead.'),
(4421, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-30', 'One Star Terrible'),
(4422, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-27', 'Excellent Coffee I absolutely love the coffee that comes from this machine.  In my opinion it makes the best homemade coffee I\'ve tasted.  I use the bold function which takes a little while but is worth it.  I use this with the hamilton Beach 80675 Permanant Gold Topne Filter 8-13 cups.  I highly recommend that filter too.  While pouring the coffee doesn\'t spill but there is always some coffee left in the carafe.  It\'s impossible to get out without turning the caraffe upside down.'),
(4423, 6, 1, 3, '2015-01-28', 'No indication on the unit or in the manual as ... No indication on the unit or in the manual as to which side is the bagel side - punch the bagel buttton and both sides keep burning.'),
(4424, 4, 1, 5, '2016-05-19', 'Five Stars love it. easy to use, good space inside, looks great!'),
(4425, 9, 1, 4, '2015-02-04', 'I really like the coffee maker and the brewed coffee is great Hoping this one will last longer than my first one did.  Other than my experience with the previous coffee maker only lasting 8 months, I really like the coffee maker and the brewed coffee is great!'),
(4426, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-30', 'Love this little workhorse! I use this blender every morning for my protein shake and take it with me for travel.  It crushes ice beautifully.  I wish I could order extra cups with lids on Amazon.  To order anywhere else, I would pay more with shipping than I do for a new blender on Amazon.'),
(4427, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-09', 'Five Stars A very good coffee maker at a great price. Brews hot coffee and keeps it that way'),
(4428, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-20', 'Five Stars It works beautifully and was delivered in a timely manner.'),
(4429, 7, 3, 5, '2014-12-28', 'follow the directions! I read hundreds of reviews for this coffee maker. My only thought is that other users were not following the very specific directions enclosed with the coffee maker. Also, those complaining about their coffee not being hot enough, I definitely do not have this problem. The coffee is very hot after being brewed. There were also reviews about how long it took the maker to work. From the time I push the on button until the coffee maker shuts off after brewing is approximately 3 minutes. Maybe I just got lucky with my Flexbrew but I LOVE IT!!!'),
(4430, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-10', 'Love it I love this coffee maker.  I make coffee in it almost every day.  It is very easy to use and I am getting rid of the coffee maker I was using.  This one is sooooooooooooo much better.'),
(4431, 5, 1, 1, '2016-08-28', 'One Star Very disappointed with this purchase.  I would not recommend this coffee maker!.'),
(4432, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Five Stars This is the best toaster oven I have ever bought!.'),
(4433, 7, 3, 5, '2014-02-28', 'It does exactly what it says it does it\'s it\'s cheaper than the Keruig machine'),
(4434, 4, 1, 5, '2016-05-25', 'Five Stars ws a gift'),
(4435, 11, 1, 5, '2014-12-15', 'Working great. As described.  Working great.'),
(4436, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-04', 'No more Starbucks for us! Makes great tasting coffee!! Handy removable water reservoir'),
(4437, 2, 1, 1, '2016-02-13', 'Sent this toaster back. Most of the time the ... Sent this toaster back.  Most of the time the timer did not work. Unless I stood over it and watched when things were done, either toasting or baking, things would burn. Also if I actually heard the timer clicking it would cut off before things were cooked. Maybe this was only a defect in this particular toaster oven but I will now try another brand.'),
(4438, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-22', 'All the toaster I\'ll ever need. I had a toaster oven for years.  I finally decided that all I really want is something that does a good job toasting my bread or bagels and I want it to do it quickly.  I made a good choice!  Yes, it\'s plastic and not high end looking like stainless is, but this little toaster does the job and does it well.  Quickly toasts bread (way faster than a toaster oven) and it\'s consistent as far as being browned on both sides.  I like that the handle pushes up so you can grab your toast without burning your fingers.  I also like the bagel setting.  You push that button when you start toasting and it only browns the cut side so the rounded side stays soft but nice and hot.  I\'ve also used the reheat function.  It will rewarm your bread without making it any darker.  The toaster looks nice on my counter and takes up a small amount of space.'),
(4439, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Color my coffee blue Love my new keurig brewer. I bought this 2.0 brewer as an addition to my other keurigs because we wanted to take a brewer on our vacation and didn\'t want to chance breaking our home brewer. It is the same quality of other products I have purchased by keurig and they continue to make my coffee experience enjoyed time and time and time again, every day. And, even though I was compelled to say, \"thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review\", I happen to believe every word'),
(4440, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-05', 'Five Stars Very good toaster.'),
(4441, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-21', 'Great item. Heats evenly and not a problem with it\'s size.  Great item.'),
(4442, 5, 1, 4, '2016-01-30', 'Good Product, Great Service This product design really solved some issues plaguing most coffeemakers.  The swing out basket and removable water tank are great!  Brewer is pretty noisy.  Needs an audible warning that the warmer timer is expiring.  Product arrived with a loose face plate that fell off after 2 days, buttons and all.  Amazon had a replacement on our doorstep 2 days after that.  Great service!'),
(4443, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-14', 'Easy to use Simple design.  Easy to use.  Love it!  Cuisinart is the best.'),
(4444, 5, 1, 3, '2014-07-14', 'Great until it dies Great coffee maker. It is easy to use and makes a great pot of coffee. The filter is very easy to change out with the convenient swinging door. About as good as it can get for a simple coffee maker. I am revising my review after 15 months of use because the coffee maker crapped out after 1 1/2 years of use. It did work well while it worked, but seemed to have a very short lifespan.'),
(4445, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-10', 'Five Stars Great toaster.'),
(4446, 10, 1, 3, '2015-02-18', 'Three Stars not very powerful'),
(4447, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-13', 'Five Stars Good product good price'),
(4448, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'great personal blender Works good and fast love how you can just drink out of'),
(4449, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-17', 'Great Little Blender I keep one at home and one at work for protein shakes.'),
(4450, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-29', 'Five Stars Best coffee maker I\'ve ever used. Replaced a Keurig with it.'),
(4451, 4, 1, 5, '2016-10-20', 'Five Stars I used it today and it works very nicely.'),
(4452, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-28', 'No, no, no A total piece of junk.  Returned.'),
(4453, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-11', 'In love! Love that you can turn off the unit without having to unplug it! The water container comes off and refills with ease and most importantly it makes HOT awesome coffee!!!'),
(4454, 5, 1, 3, '2016-09-06', 'Ok, then It makes coffee. The features work as advertised. Acceptable value for the money.'),
(4455, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-22', 'Five Stars Works great, gave it for a gift and they love it!!'),
(4456, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-05', 'Love it!! Amazing! Looks exactly like the picture! It\'s great and portable! Very conveinent and the quality is great!'),
(4457, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-25', 'best coffeemaker ever! I have fallen in love with this coffee maker. Ignore the complaints about the plastic smell/taste. If you clean it thoroughly on the first day (yes, it\'s a hassle, but use vinegar and it\'ll go faster), then it\'s a nonissue. I do wish it beeped when the coffee was done the way some coffee makers do, but that\'s my only complaint. The water reservoir is so well designed that I can\'t believe how stupid all the other coffee makers in the world are for not following suit.'),
(4458, 3, 1, 2, '2016-09-09', 'It was to large for the area I needed it ... It was to large for the area I needed it for. I had to buy another at a store.'),
(4459, 4, 1, 4, '2015-05-31', 'Very easy to clean I use this almost every day and for any meal.  Very easy to clean, except the top on the inside.  It is easy to use and looks nice in the kitchen.'),
(4460, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-23', 'Optional use of charcoal Filter and Removal Tank I\'m very satisfied with this purchase.  I bought this coffeemaker because of the removal water tank and optional use of charcoal.  I would have liked having the charcoal filter as on other coffeemakers, but having the option to use or not to use worked better for me.  The brewing time is slightly longer than my previous coffeemakers.'),
(4461, 6, 1, 3, '2014-08-26', 'This toaster is a nice looking unit This toaster is a nice looking unit.  Nothing terribly fancy.  As some others have noted, the elements do not glow evenly thus producing uneven heat.  But for the price it still does a decent job.'),
(4462, 8, 1, 4, '2016-02-28', 'Otherwise it is a very nice coffeemaker for the price It works well.  The only problem with it is it doesn\'t stop brewing when you pull the pot out to pour that first \"desperately needed\" cup of coffee.  Otherwise it is a very nice coffeemaker for the price.'),
(4463, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-27', 'Five Stars Wow, most evenly toasted toast I ever seen, it was prefect!!!'),
(4464, 6, 1, 3, '2015-04-16', 'Three Stars Flimsier than all my other Cuisinart appliances or cookware.'),
(4465, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-17', 'Our favorite coffee maker we\'ve ever had! We purchased ours roughly a year and a half ago.  We had stayed at a resort that had one in the room.  We loved the whole concept of no carafe.  It is also very easy to clean the internal tank that acts as the carafe.  The power cord is also great to where you can adjust to an exact length by pushing in the excess cord back under the maker.  This coffee maker has performed flawlessly and the coffee is brewed to perfection.  If I had to mention anything I would change, would be the auto shutoff may be a little too soon.  I\'d add another hour.'),
(4466, 4, 1, 1, '2015-10-15', 'Faulty Toaster My toaster broke after only a year of use. The unit started staying on even when it was turned off. It will only turn off now if we unplug the toaster. I don\'t recommend this faulty toaster at all.'),
(4467, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-10', 'great It does everything I expected it to and so much more. Looks like a more expensive appliance than it really is.'),
(4468, 11, 1, 3, '2014-01-02', 'ok for the price I really, really, really loved my Breville toaster/convection oven but when it had an  electircal blow-out after only 2 years, I had to settle on a less expensive toaster oven. I miss my Breville but this substitute is ok for heating food, toasting English muffins etc, and reheating leftovers. Use the toaster option carefully because it burns toast easily.'),
(4469, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-21', 'Five Stars Makes decent coffee, it\'s small and convenient.'),
(4470, 3, 1, 4, '2015-04-29', 'Great appliance! I have carried on for the longest ... Great appliance!  I have carried on for the longest about purchasing a toaster oven and I\'m glad I waited for this one.  Like a microwave, there are a number of pre-programmed features plus the convection feature that makes  the use of this oven really easy and enjoyable.  The food cooks to perfection - pizza, chicken, and biscuits are the only  foods I have prepared so far, but I couldn\'t be happier with the results.  As opposed to my stove oven, the fact that I can program the amount of time my food cooks is such a bonus  I no longer need to feel tied to  the kitchen, I can set the time and go about my house work.  I highly recommend this item.'),
(4471, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Perfect for on the go-ers in the morning like me Perfect for on the go-ers in the morning like me! Easy to use and clean up is a breeze!'),
(4472, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', 'A real time & energy saver I love this toaster oven so much I put my regular toaster away. Huge variety of settings and now I don\'t need to turn on my huge oven and preheat it for 20 minutes in order to cook something small.'),
(4473, 6, 1, 4, '2014-10-03', 'Four Stars Works just as expected.'),
(4474, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'Five Stars Heats quickly and toasts evenly. Hard to beat for the price.'),
(4475, 9, 1, 3, '2015-01-21', 'For some reason this coffee maker leaks really bad. Have walked into the kitchen and the whole ... For some reason this coffee maker leaks really bad. Have walked into the kitchen and the whole contents are on the counter and floor.'),
(4476, 7, 3, 3, '2016-01-27', 'I bought this two days ago. OK after about 4 tries I got a cup of coffee. I tried the K Cups first. Instead of piercing the bottom like a Kuerig, it tore a gash in the side and the coffee was very, Very, strong. Mind you I have been using these same K- Cups until my Kuerig Broke (after 3 years of great coffee). The second k-cup worked OK, so then I thought I would use the Filter and make Ground Coffee, I used some \"Seattle\'s Best\" in the basket and I put in 2 scoops, It frothed out all over the counter, the cup and the machine, grounds everywhere. I threw that cup away and tried One Scoop. Same thing Happened but not as bad. so then I thought maybe I should use the little basket that says it is for fine grind coffee (Which it was not) That worked OK with one scoop, Maybe Now I can try for 2 scoops. So now I guess I can make coffee, but it will have to be K-Cups, or Weak. Another thing is the reservoir only holds 10 OZ. of water I drink a 12 OZ. Mug so I get a Half Cup, Sometimes you have to turn it back on to finish brewing the 10 OZ. because it will shut off after about 6 or 8 OZ. I tried adding another 2 Oz. water during brewing to make a full cup. I guess I can make it work, but if it gives me too much trouble back it goes.'),
(4477, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-12', 'Powerful Little Thing I really like my little toaster oven. It tends to be a little more powerful than the settings suggest...So if you\'re making toast, don\'t leave it or it will burn. Other than that, I\'ve been baking and warming things in it and it\'s worked great. Be careful not to touch the top or put anything on the top that can melt. It gets VERY hot.'),
(4478, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'Great so far! So far so good.  I really love my new Keurig and the ease of brewing the coffee & tea.  It\'s quick and convenient and so much less mess & clean up than my regular coffeemaker.  I think its great that you can adjust the size and the strength.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4479, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Five Stars Super'),
(4480, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'We love this coffee maker We love this coffee maker. Over the years, we have been through many different coffee makers, but we think the water reservoir is awesome; it really cuts down on time and the odds of making a mess. If there was one flaw that had to be noted is the fact that we are used to the ability to have a 4 hour automatic shutoff instead of this units static 2 hour factory default. We are slowly getting used to it, but we are still forgetting to reset the unit from time to time. Having said that, if we were buying a new coffee maker today, it would be this model.'),
(4481, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-21', 'Good option/good price Works great.  Easy to use as oven. Wish is was a bit easier to clean. You cannot remove the heating element, so have to clean around it.'),
(4482, 1, 1, 1, '2015-08-28', 'Not consistant nor reliable. I purchased one of these k250s to replace my old fashion standard coffee maker. I ended up returning it because we were getting coffee grounds in every cup. I figured I just had a bad machine so I got another k250. After one month the same problem was happening. In fact it seemed as though the machine didn\'t know when it was done brewing and coffee grounds were everywhere when I would make a second cup. This K250 is going back and I\'m getting something else.'),
(4483, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'Nice machine This was indeed a great coffee machine. Thanks to all the reviewers, I never spill coffee finally and the blue screen looks pretty.'),
(4484, 8, 1, 3, '2015-10-13', '5 cups? Nah. 2 1/2 cups. Works ... 5 cups?  Nah. 2 1/2 cups. Works well. Needs an auto shutoff.'),
(4485, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-04', 'Five Stars as advertised.'),
(4486, 2, 1, 3, '2016-04-26', 'Mixed feelings Bought this to replace a 20-year-old TRO200 model that finally gave up the ghost. I understand that the timer/ding and multiple knobs are probably due to safety features implemented in those 20 years, but it seems overly complicated to use. Another probably safety-related change that I don\'t like is that the rack is a lot higher up inside this model, so I can no longer fit a standard loaf pan inside. (I bought a shallower pan for baking cornbread, etc.) And the trays that fit inside the old model are about 1/4 inch too wide to go into this oven -- you can kind of force them in but they don\'t really sit level. Mostly I guess I just miss my old toaster oven! They definitely don\'t make small appliances like that any more. This one looks nice but I guarantee it won\'t last 20 years.'),
(4487, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-13', 'I\'ve had my \"little red machine\" for just over a week now. I use it quite frequently. I love it. It\'s become that I\'m the only one in the house who drinks coffee so making an entire pot for myself became a little much. This little machine is perfect. It\'s brew time (according to the owner\'s manual is about 4 min) it seems a little quicker than that but what\'s 4 min when you\'ve other things to be doing. Coffee, tea, cider cocoa. Doesn\'t matter what you\'re making. It\'s always perfect. I\'ve read other reviews before purchasing; and thought either this was a faulty product or just bad usage. I believe bad usage in part. With you k cups you need to make certain that not only you push the cup down into the basket but that you push the handle down into the cup. Bare in mind these units are not meant to be used with the \"new 2.0\" models. IF you have issues with the cups then pre-poke the top. Problem, solved.'),
(4488, 7, 3, 1, '2015-09-20', 'Never worked the way I expected. Never returned the same amount of water that I put in. It made a ton of noise but quite before using all the water. I will be returning it and not buying a Hewitt Packard again...'),
(4489, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-08', 'Temperature was nice and hot I finished setting up my Keurig.  After reading some reviews and read about all the stuff that was included, I thought I was was going to have to spend an hour setting this thing up with the filter and doing a descaling and rinsing out bin. But I found the LETS GET STARTED guide.  All it said was to rinse out the water bin, fill up bin and press BREW to  run hot water through machine. That\'s it. you\'re ready to brew!  yes it did come with descaling solution and a water filter and some other little accessories.  Didn\'t bother reading into it yet.  I\'m sure the filter attaches to the bin inside.  There is a connector for it. As for the descaling solution, I think it\'s for cleaning out the machine after some use. I\'ll read the manual later.  For now, LET\'S GET BREW\'IN!! Popped in a K-cup and did my first brew.  Temperature was nice and hot.  Coffee came out nice and dark, bold--just how I like it. As for those who are dangling whether to purchase this or not because of the K-cup issue.  I say buy it!  Most selections out there are already Keurig \"certified\".  The brand you\'re drinking now is probably already certified.'),
(4490, 8, 1, 1, '2016-03-12', 'Dependable Coffee Maker - that leaks coffee all the time. Pros: 1. Affordable This coffee maker is so affordable such that I was able to buy one for myself, another one as backup, totally paid out of pocket for my office, and donated one to the graduate student lounge. 2. Works It makes coffee 3. Dependable Like a Honda Civic, except it makes coffee. Cons: 1 out of 3 times it \"leaks\" coffee when I pour coffee out of it into a mug. 1 out of 2 times that happens when I \"normally\" pour coffee. 1 out of 1 time (aka always) leaks coffee when pour it in the morning before rush hours.'),
(4491, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Great Machine! Been a Keurig user for several years, love the new2.0 k250. Its very easy to use, hot coffee and good flavor. Thanks to Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(4492, 9, 1, 4, '2017-01-20', 'I like it. Works good.  The water reservoir doesn\'t detach very easily and probably could use a handle like my last coffee maker.'),
(4493, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'Five Stars This is the BEST!'),
(4494, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'Five Stars Perfect'),
(4495, 6, 1, 2, '2015-02-15', 'Takes to long to toast. Sometimes doesn\'t even defrost ... Takes to long to toast.  Sometimes doesn\'t even defrost inside of a small bagel.'),
(4496, 6, 1, 1, '2016-02-22', 'Poor quality This is a very poor quality toaster. It\'s all over the place in terms of heat--one day undercooks and the next burns the bread on the same setting. My ten dollar toaster from Target worked better than this and took up less space.'),
(4497, 12, 1, 5, '2015-06-14', 'Five Stars Love it!!!!!'),
(4498, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'So far K250 works quite well. It took a ... So far K250 works quite well. It took a few tries to get the right coffee blend for my taste but the convenience of the Brewer compensates.'),
(4499, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Good coffee maker Sooo much better than I expected.'),
(4500, 8, 1, 1, '2014-12-30', 'Water pump died after 6 uses I purchased this coffee pot about a year ago and it worked fabulously the 6 times that I used it. Now the pump doesn\'t work. I\'m very disappointed that I bought a product that only worked 6 times before it broke. :('),
(4501, 6, 1, 4, '2014-05-02', 'Works well No issues or problems up to this point, I have had this unit for about six months now and is still working well'),
(4502, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-29', 'Five Stars Excellent'),
(4503, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-17', 'Five Stars The best toaster I have ever had...'),
(4504, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-14', 'I Love It It works great. I am not a heavy user so this one would do. Can\'t beat the price.'),
(4505, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-12', 'I really enjoy breakfast smoothies with this I really enjoy breakfast smoothies with this. My children also enjoy homemade slushies with it as well.  Inexpensive and good quality'),
(4506, 1, 1, 1, '2016-10-14', 'I really hate this coffee maker I really hate this coffee maker.  Just bought 2 identical boxes of coffee cups at Trader Joes specifically designated as \"\"for use with Keurig K-cup\" One box works with Keurig, the other gives me the stupid \"Oops you are trying to cheat Keurig and we won\'t make your coffee for you\" message. I don\'t care if the Trader Joes K-cups are slightly out of spec.  I still blame Keurig.  I hate the whole system.  They make enough money selling me a coffee maker, I resent it that they have to have a monopoly on the K-cups.  Plus the darn thing is way too finicky and requires way too much maintenance.  I strongly recommend against Keurig, a terrible product.'),
(4507, 8, 1, 1, '2016-07-28', 'Amazon should be better than this! Just received my package.  When I opened the Amazon box, I couldn\'t believe how badly damaged the Black & Decker box was.  I have no idea whether the actual coffee maker is damaged, but obviously the product was not handled with care.  The power cord was not even secured with a band or twist tie.  It was loosely laid in the box.  Obviously a return that they just passed off to someone else.  You get what you pay for.'),
(4508, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-22', 'Five Stars Definately best coffee pot I have ever owned...'),
(4509, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-06', 'Five Stars What I wanted.'),
(4510, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-27', 'Four Stars Very good but beware, This is the 2.0 version so check before you buy anything for it!'),
(4511, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-15', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker so much better then my last one'),
(4512, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-08', 'Five Stars Works great.'),
(4513, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-10', 'It ispretty good product. Only tray inside is not robust enough ... It ispretty good product.Only tray inside is not robust enough as I expected.'),
(4514, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-10', 'Horrible, horrible piece of junk This thing is a piece of JUNK.  Bought it Nov 2014, elements on both sides burnt out.  Horrible, horrible piece of junk.  Starts burning and is a fire hazard.  I threw out my old one and wished I had not.  Cheaply made, very cheaply.  I have not overused it, I just like toast every couple of days.'),
(4515, 4, 1, 4, '2016-03-07', 'Safety issue Upper elements would not turn off!  Had to unplug.  A serious safety issue.'),
(4516, 4, 1, 1, '2016-07-31', 'Cuisinart TOB-40 The only reason I keep this Toaster Oven Broiler is that it\'s the smallest one available - (my kitchen was a butler\'s pantry).  Original model, TOB-40 SN:30608 previously purchased, was rendered inoperable by hot water pipe bursting in sink.  It rated 3 &1/2 stars because compared to my little Kenmore TOB it required more positions of oven rack, broil rack, and bake pan, and took more fiddling around to get proper toasting.  The \"new\" model TOB-40 SN:60322  is different from the previous TOB-40 - has ceramic? knobs on ends of heating rods, two metal projections on the outside bottom left side of toaster, is not level (had to put wedge under on side, has no broil rack (bake pan has to be manipulated into oven rack), bangs when heating up and cooling down, and burns bread at very light setting! See old vs. new oven views.'),
(4517, 2, 1, 1, '2016-07-29', 'Terrible. Timer dial very hard to turn Terrible. Timer dial very hard to turn. The position of the \"stay on\" is a poor design. Returned item.'),
(4518, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-10', 'Five Stars works great and looks dreat'),
(4519, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-28', 'I just love this single cup brewer. Makes a quick cup of coffee so quickly. Excellent price Strong durable product!'),
(4520, 10, 1, 3, '2015-04-21', 'Three Stars good for a diet shake in the AM. NOT heavy duty. serves it\'s purpose'),
(4521, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-21', 'Poor design The product is poorly designed and when the water container is filled to 12 cups the coffee pot overflows and spills all over the counter. Plus, there is no option to disable the \"auto off\" function so the coffee gets cold if you don\'t drink the whole pot within the 2 hour period.'),
(4522, 5, 1, 3, '2016-01-30', 'Nice compact, low priced, average coffee maker PROS: I like the size of this coffee maker--quite narrow. I like the removable water reservoir. CONS: The coffee it makes is perfectly average--nothing special.  To make it taste much better use the Bold setting.  But this takes forever.  I don\'t like that you can\'t force the \"Keep Warm\" function to stay on--it just shuts off after some unknown period.  My spouse get up early and I get up later and often the coffee is cold.  This coffee maker is extremely noisy. It is better than the Cuisinart it replaced but itself is likely to be replaced soon--it is \"serviceable\" the way driving a Chevy sedan will get you where you need to go.  But I am still looking for my Mercedes quality, quiet, and features.'),
(4523, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Hamilton Beach 22708-the perfect toaster/oven We Love this toaster/oven.  It is a perfect size, being slightly larger than a toaster but way smaller than a small counter oven. It toasts and bakes beautifully. It is an all in one toaster/oven with a great design. Easy to clean. Does everything it says it does.  We purchased this model rather than the newer model because the tray is attached to the door so when you open the door the contents in the oven are easy to remove.  No burned fingers! Some things just don\'t come out the same when you use a microwave especially bread, eg warm sandwiches.  We got this toaster/oven on the recommendation of our daughter who raved about all of the above features.'),
(4524, 8, 1, 4, '2016-03-21', 'Four Stars works well'),
(4525, 1, 1, 4, '2015-09-20', 'Works well. Feels cheap compared to the k45. ... Works well. Feels cheap compared to the k45. Pointless display, imo. Does not have auto off feature. The real kicker is that you have to take the base off to fit a normal sized coffee cup. Not a huge deal, but the machines always drip a little after and nothing is there to catch it unless you use a small mug. I would rather own the k45. I may return this model, I haven\'t decided.'),
(4526, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-28', 'Love been using this over a year and 0 problems so far. Love it'),
(4527, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Four Stars Wish it had larger brew capacity'),
(4528, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-23', 'Five Stars Love it.'),
(4529, 6, 1, 5, '2014-05-08', 'Worth the  price At last I have a toaster that looks and feels sturdy and does a decent job. It is so easy to use to get good results and I like the  different settings to take out the guess work. If you are looking for a new toaster and are fed up with buying cheap and short lived products from Wxxmxxt then I recommend you take a look at this one.'),
(4530, 9, 1, 1, '2015-11-24', 'Brews coffee all over the counter I purchased this after several days of reading reviews of various coffee makers. After a string of bad luck with coffee pots, I thought this was the one. Boy, was I wrong. The first brew was great. The first cup of the day is often gotten in a dark kitchen, so I really liked the light that comes when dispensing coffee. All subsequent brews were disastrous. The valve/gasket that opens to dispense coffee didn\'t close fully, so the second pot of coffee brewed all over the kitchen counter and onto the floor. I fiddled with it to make sure there wasn\'t a blockage, but all subsequent uses resulted in leaks. I followed the instructions for use exactly to make sure it wasn\'t anything I was doing wrong. Each time I brewed coffee I returned the coffee maker and obtained a replacement, and that one did the same thing. Even IF the thing didn\'t leak everywhere, this still would not be the coffee maker for me; the instructions say to use 1 spoonful (spoon included) of coffee per cup, using no more than 14 spoonfuls. That doesn\'t leave much room for adjustment when you want to brew 12 cups of strong coffee.'),
(4531, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-03', 'Five Stars we are very pleased with this oven and would recommend it to others.'),
(4532, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'Great buy I have truly enjoyed this coffee maker'),
(4533, 5, 1, 1, '2014-04-03', 'GARBAGE BASED ON DURABILITY, formerly Very Good--In Comparison To Others Pros: The carafe no drip spout works well. Heats water to a hot temperature. Easy to add water. Carafe removable during brewing. No leaks. Cons: Proprietary size of carafe means any existing carafes won\'t work. Residue of fresh ground coffee consistently escapes filters. Coffee brewers are not made to the standards they were 20 or 30 years ago, largely due to their manufacture in China.  The pros outweigh the cons of this coffee make but I don\'t love it and the proprietary size of the carafe limits the ability to use other carafes to brew tea, etc. REVIEW AMENDED MAY 19, 2014. I BOUGHT THIS COFFEE MAKER JUNE 11, 2013 AND IT DIED TODAY.  A COFFEE MAKER SHOULD LAST FIVE YEARS OR MORE.  MANY MODERN COFFEE MAKERS DO NOT LAST AND IT IS A REFLECTION OF CHEAP MANUFACTURING STANDARDS IN CHINA. We will now try our FOURTH Coffee Maker in 41 Months. Oh, and while the product comes with a one year \"warranty\" you are responsible for the cost of returning the coffee maker and the cost of them sending you a new one.  That\'s about the cost of the new Mr. Coffee unit we are ordering.  If corporations are people Hamilton Beach deserves a good swift kick front and rear.'),
(4534, 12, 1, 4, '2017-01-27', 'Very good for this price It works fine; not very well made in that the door doesn\'t close snugly and the baking tray doesn\'t fit precisely onto the grill (when you close the door and the grill slides back, the tray dislodges).  But for $29 it\'s worth it.'),
(4535, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-12', 'Five Stars Great my grandson love it'),
(4536, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Great coffee Makes great coffee had trouble with paper filters used the wire ones works great easy the set clock and timer would but again.'),
(4537, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-16', 'The Keurig coffee brewer is satisfying. After owning our Keurig brewer for 2  weeks, my husband and I enjoyed our 1st cup of coffee today.  Unfortunately, it wasn\'t as simple as it appears to be, brewing a cup or carafe of coffee. Upon receiving proper instructions from the professionals at Keurig, we decided we would keep the brewer. \"Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(4538, 8, 1, 5, '2014-11-24', 'Super for Instant Coffee or as a hot water maker for tea I use coffee in single cup packets. The packets require you to empty the contents in hot water and stir so what I really needed was a quick and easy hot water maker. I looked at hot water kettles but the reviews of those had drawbacks from flimsy construction to rusting. So I bought and tried this. It works great with instant coffee and it is very low cost. Just put the instant coffee in the plastic filter basket with NO PAPER FILTER. The coffee maker has a shower head type water sprayer that sprays hot water into the filter basket. This effectively and thoroughly dissolves the coffee and when it goes into the carafe it is ready to drink. I actually place a big mug under the spout instead of the included carafe and I don\'t have to even pour. I place a large 20oz mug under the spout. I pour water into the coffee maker to the 3.5 cup level. In a short while the cup is full and the coffee is actually darker and stronger than it would be if I just put the coffee in hot water and stirred. The one packet is supposed to make one cup (5 to 8 oz) but I use the one pack to make about 16oz. The coffee is dark and strong enough for me. So this works fantastic as a substitute for a hot water maker for instant coffee such as Organo Gold or other instant coffees.'),
(4539, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Can Get started in The Morning without our Keurig !!! We are very happy with our new Keruig 2.0. We can still choose cup sizes and everything else that we did with our old Keruig. The carafe is a great asset too for when we are having breakfast and need that second cup.  When you register your Keurig brewer online they send you a code for two free boxes of k cups when you purchase two along with free shipping also. Thank you Keriug for the free pods for this review.'),
(4540, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-09', 'Four Stars A ok.'),
(4541, 3, 1, 4, '2015-05-08', 'Four Stars works great looks ok, but handles the pizzas nicely'),
(4542, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-30', 'Five Stars Nice and sturdy'),
(4543, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-04', 'excellent! Boys will be Boys and for a Boy to have one of these in his room in College has made him a hero....excellent!'),
(4544, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Pretty Good For The Price My mom\'s been using this lately for making shakes. So far it\'s pretty good for it\'s price. She\'s happy with this.'),
(4545, 5, 1, 3, '2015-09-09', 'Seems nice enough Purchased this coffee maker and it\'s okay. I can program it til 6 cups which is half the other coffee makers make. No leaks and great for brewing my concoction. I can smell the aroma of the coffee. Seems nice enough'),
(4546, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-26', 'Five Stars Easy to use and not consume large space'),
(4547, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-21', 'Five Stars makes toast. and other stuff.'),
(4548, 7, 3, 4, '2016-06-02', 'I just bought this flex brew. I bought it because of the flexibility of being able to use both k-cups and ground coffee. It is also advertised as being able to be used with both travel mugs and coffee cups. This is true they will both fit under the brew system, but it only makes 8 oz of coffee. Now unless your travel cup is a lot smaller than mine you are still only getting a coffee cup full of coffee. Now let me also say that this 8 oz is not going to fill your cup to the brim, unless maybe you are using tea cups instead of today\'s coffee mugs. Now this is fine for me because it leaves room for creamer at the top. So to sum it up I recommend this for anyone that likes a cup of coffee or two and likes to use regular size coffee mugs.'),
(4549, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-14', 'Great This little unit is awsome.  I toast, make cheese melts, heat leftovers all in one little unit that doesn\'t take up much counter space.  Great product'),
(4550, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-10', 'B & D longstanding quality name, great price, works well, easy on the eye and pocketbook! Got oven in ONE day! Easy to assemple, plugged it in, have a small pizza doing quite nicely right this moment!.'),
(4551, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-14', 'Three Stars gets very hot. must be careful touching exterior. however functions well and is cheaply priced'),
(4552, 1, 1, 1, '2015-09-26', 'I love keurig and I was so sad when our old ... If I could give 0 stars I would! We are on our 2nd keurig 250 2.0 and we won\'t be buying another. It either blows out the K cup and you end up with a cup full of grounds or it takes an hour for it to brew an entire cup. It also has a hard time recognizing k cups, the screen will tell us it\'s not a keurig cup even though it says clearly, keurig. I love keurig and I was so sad when our old one quit but I\'m done trying to return these things.'),
(4553, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Five Stars definitely a space saver, considering my small kitchen.  it\'s small for a toaster over but gets the job done.'),
(4554, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-09', 'His old Black and Decker had the toaster lever and he never had any difficulties with the toast coming out perfect. I bought this toaster for my Grandfather. He really needs the toast lever (switch). He has difficulty turning the toast knob to the correct adjustment. His old Black and Decker had the toaster lever and he never had any difficulties with the toast coming out perfect.'),
(4555, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-14', 'Good price It`s a simple coffer maker. Perfect size for two Marks and save some counter space. Bought some paper filters, added ground coffee half way up to the filter, added water all the way to the maximum. I used it about 5 days. No complain.'),
(4556, 10, 1, 4, '2016-01-27', 'I received the unit in good condition and after running it through the dishwasher I received the unit in good condition and after running it through the dishwasher, it was near lunchtime, so the first thing i decided to make in it was tuna salad. I dumped two cans of tuna, mayonaisse, some left over chopped celery and onion, pickle relish and a bit of lemon juice into the 16 oz Ninja conatiner, pulsed it a few times and out came an excellent tuna salad suitable for spreading on sandwiches. It took less than 10 minutes and I had enough for four sandwiches. Since then I have made fresh salsa, bruschetta and other similar goodies. All have turned out well. This product does exactly what it says it will do.'),
(4557, 11, 1, 4, '2014-02-05', 'Simple toaster oven I got this a few weeks ago.  So far, I have toasted bread and frozen waffles, grilled red peppers (cut up, it\'s not big enough to fit the whole pepper in), defrosted frozen items at a very low temp, and heated up leftovers.  Takes up very little counter space.  I am trying to reduce my utility bills, so like that it doesn\'t use much energy.  Very even toasting, like advertised!  But, burns toast easily if you leave it on too long, so I set the temp to 400 when I toast.  CAUTION:  it gets hot on the outside while cooking, though it cools off very fast once you turn it off. The only thing that I don\'t like is that you have to tilt the tray that catches the crumbs at the bottom to get it out, which spills the crumbs on the bottom which is not removable, so if I ever made a big mess it might be a little awkward to clean.  But overall, great little toaster oven.'),
(4558, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-21', 'Five Stars This is a great little toaster. Works as advertised. I have had it for one year now.'),
(4559, 8, 1, 5, '2015-01-21', 'Five Stars good little item'),
(4560, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Five Stars Very good'),
(4561, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-22', 'Five Stars really great for those morning shakes.'),
(4562, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'What a smooth little blender...........small and wonderful Where we stay in Florida (Indian Shores) the company have kindly placed a large Hamilton Beach Blender in every flat. I like it so much I bought the small one for my breakfast smoothies. Absolutely great. Individual size and small enough to carry around, for vacations. Thanks Hamilton Beach! What was also wonderful was the speed it was delivered to Indian Shores. I paid a little extra and it arrived the day after we did. Thanks Amazon'),
(4563, 9, 1, 4, '2016-04-08', 'slow pour The only reason it did not get five stars.... takes too long to fill my cup. like 15-20 seconds. Needs to be like 4-5 seconds. Drives me nuts for some reason.'),
(4564, 5, 1, 2, '2015-05-03', 'Doesn\'t Get Hot Enough I\'m working with them to resolve an issue of it not getting hot enough ~ 150 degrees is not enough to bring out the best in the coffee.'),
(4565, 9, 1, 1, '2016-08-06', 'Not happy:( So while the thought of having coffee on demand is appealing, the coffee it produces is very bad.  The basket the coffee sits in is plastic so you can taste the plastic chemicals in the coffee. In addition it is not as hot as I am used to so I usually microwave it after pouring. I\'m going back to my pure, but time consuming, chemix coffee maker!.'),
(4566, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker. Very easy to program and brews a mean cup of joe! Great price as well.'),
(4567, 5, 1, 4, '2015-01-06', 'I really like this coffee pot I really like this coffee pot.  Instead of filling the carafe, the water reservoir pops off to fill directly.  Saves me from water all over my counter!  It is sleek.  It does brew a little slow, but I am spoiled by the commercial Bunn we have at work.  Would recommend this for any home user.'),
(4568, 12, 1, 1, '2014-02-24', 'Poor Quality Having owned one of these in the past, I didn\'t hesitate to get another one when the first finally quit working, after years of service. Much to my dismay, the new toaster is of poor quality. The toast is either burned or only half done. The mechanism inside is lopsided, leading me to think it\'s a production issue. The actual metal parts are lopsided. Stay away from this product. You\'ll be replacing it within a short time. Not worth the money.'),
(4569, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-09', 'Five Stars Love it!!!!!!!!!!'),
(4570, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Five Stars Exactly what i was looking for. This thing Rocks and the price is great'),
(4571, 8, 1, 4, '2016-07-22', 'Great size for a bachelor Great size for a bachelor! Nice, simple little coffee pot, but no auto-off timer precludes me from really enjoying it fully. I ended up getting a slightly too big coffee maker simply because I didn\'t want to scorch another pot, and maybe start a fire...maybe. I\'m recovering from a brain injury, so the piece of mind from a auto-off pot wins out in the end. Would be perfect for work or a small family.'),
(4572, 5, 1, 2, '2014-07-31', 'Not a quality product at all! Nine months and it\'s malfunctioning.  The heating element is rusted, and now it\'s brewing on strong, despite having it set to regular strength.  Very disappointed with this coffee maker.'),
(4573, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-14', 'My Morning friend Makes it taste excellent.'),
(4574, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-01', 'Toaster Oven Love it! Works great! Nice looking too!.'),
(4575, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-11', 'This is a really nice coffee maker This is a really nice coffee maker. The overall build quality is excellent. And the design is smart. Use and cleanup are much easier than other inexpensive coffee makers that I have owned. The features that impress me the most are the lift-out water tank and the adjustable carafe heat control. I did a bunch of research before I bought this machine. Once I narrowed it down to four or five coffee makers that I really liked, this one was the only one that sold for less than $90.00. For the money, I don\'t think that this machine has any true competition.'),
(4576, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-19', 'Five Stars This was amazing!'),
(4577, 4, 1, 1, '2017-01-08', 'Stay away! I have this model, not purchased through Amazon. The lower heating elements stopped working, and when I looked inside, the front lower element has split open and warped. It looks very dangerous, certainly a fire hazard. Up to this point I liked it. There is no recall on this product despite other reviews I found on internet searches. The company has assured me that they have fixed this, and are replacing the unit with a 10.00 shipping charge.'),
(4578, 4, 1, 5, '2016-04-21', 'Five Stars enjoying every day'),
(4579, 4, 1, 2, '2015-07-08', 'Died after 2 years. This toaster worked well for one and a half years. Then the lower heating elements began to change shape and glow strangely. there was never any damage to them, they seemed to be melting from their own heat. After a few months of this gradual deformation the lower elements stopped working entirely.  This looks to me like planned obsolescence.'),
(4580, 9, 1, 4, '2016-07-09', 'Fast as a Bunn Almost everything great with this coffee maker. Only con is it has a super short plug. Have to unplug it everyday before I can use it. Pkug in is about 3 inches.'),
(4581, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-01', 'Great Coffee Maker with lots of convenience and options I always wait several months before writing a review, and I have to say that this coffee maker is exactly as advertised. I love it. The convenience of the separate water tank is awesome. Easy to remove and fill. I like that you don\'t have to use the carafe to do it. The swing out coffee basket is the same. All of this makes it so you don\'t have to move the coffee maker itself. Finally, there are a host of options: Brewing strength, length the warmer stays on, temperature of the warmer. Finally, I like the look of it as it sits on our kitchen counter. I would buy again.'),
(4582, 10, 1, 4, '2016-04-01', 'I dumped two cans of tuna, mayonaisse, some left over chopped celery and onion I dumped two cans of tuna, mayonaisse, some left over chopped celery and onion, pickle relish and a bit of lemon juice into the 16 oz Ninja conatiner, pulsed it a few times and out came an excellent tuna salad suitable for spreading on sandwiches. It took less than 10 minutes and I had enough for four sandwiches.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(4583, 2, 1, 3, '2015-03-31', 'it is kind of annoying to have to spin all the dials for each ... It\'s a decent product for the price.  I\'m not sure there\'s truly such a thing as a toaster that toasts bread completely evenly.  Certainly not in the (affordable) price range that we\'re interested in purchasing.  It does a decent enough job; it\'s only toast, this is not Cordon Bleu cooking.  While the unit works reasonably well, it does have some challenges.  If you\'re a bit older, you might find all the markings on the three function dials a bit hard to read.  In fact, it is kind of annoying to have to spin all the dials for each use when you are changing from \"toast,\" to \"bake,\" to even just \"warm.\"  Too much messing around to get the function you want.  And then, of course, you\'ll need to keep your glasses handy to read the very small black-on-silver writing or symbols that indicate what it is you are choosing to accomplish with this toaster-oven.  The one significant problem with this unit is that the bottom selection dial requires you to spin it completely past the 10-minute mark and then have to turn it again back counter-clockwise to get to the color of toast you want.  This dial turns easily enough in the clockwise direction.  But in counter-clockwise direction (which you MUST use to get back to the desired toast color), this dial is extremely hard to grip and turn.  My wife needs to get out the rubber dishwashing gloves in order to grip this dial well enough to turn it counter-clockwise.  Even for me it is a difficult grip and turn.  I will probably install something sticky or grippy to be able to get this function dial to turn more easily going counter-clockwise.  So...in order to make toast you have to set 3 dials--which seems a bit excessive.  On our old Black and Decker, the toast color was permanently set, and all you needed to do was hit the start button.  Also on the old one, if you wanted to bake, all you did was turn the separate oven temperature dial.  You didn\'t have to reset all these functions like you do on this one.  It\'s just annoying, that\'s all.  It does make very good bake potatoes.  Our old Black and Decker quit after about 12 years, so we\'ll see how this one does.  It\'s OK...but not great.'),
(4584, 4, 1, 5, '2016-04-24', 'Five Stars Love this oven! Works really well and cleans super easily. LOVE the crumb tray!!'),
(4585, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-20', 'Least expensive coffee maker I\'ve bought for a long time - and the best This is a great machine and I\'ve had zero issues with it.  Bought this last March after my latest expensive Cuisinart machine decided it had worked long enough. It is very well designed and made.  Being able to easily separate the reservoir and fill it at the sink is a refreshing change from having to use a flashlight to see how much water I needed to pour into the Cuisinart.  Also very easy to take basket out to clean.  Carafe is good about not making a mess when you take it out in mid cycle.  The only, very minor, gripe I have is that there is a lip at the top of the carafe that makes it a little less easy to clean it out after use. Notwithstanding, this is easily the best coffee maker I\'ve had vs. much more expensive and less intuitive units from Krups, Braun and Cuisinart.  I\'m glad that Hamilton Beach seems to spend their $$ on engineering and product development instead of on marketing.'),
(4586, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-02', 'Four Stars doesn\'t have a timer - otherwise great'),
(4587, 7, 3, 5, '2015-12-30', 'Please read the directions carefully, the first time you use it....I put a tad more water than directed and ended up with a mess, but after that I measured carefully and have been completely satisfied....it really does make a great cup of coffee...the price was great, well designed and I love it!'),
(4588, 8, 1, 5, '2015-12-18', 'nice, inexpensive littl epot very nice pot,  small and takes up little room, I got it to make tea to steep for iced tea. My only complaint is with me, as i tend to over-pour the pot and make it drip when I am pouring the condensed tea out into the pitcher of water'),
(4589, 6, 1, 1, '2015-12-15', 'Rip Off Bought this toaster in black. It only toasts 1 side of the bread, the other side is white or slightly barely toasted. For 29 bucks, what a rip off.  Bought it from Bed Bath & Beyond. I do not fault the store, I fault Cuisinart.'),
(4590, 6, 1, 2, '2015-12-03', 'Two Stars does not defrost or toast properly, burns even on loe numbers'),
(4591, 10, 1, 3, '2015-06-08', 'It\'s the size I wanted and works fine. I use it to only make smoothies for ... It\'s the size I wanted and works fine. I use it to only make smoothies for my son. It however makes some loud grumbling noise even when it just has liquids in it. I had the same model before and I don\'t remember this pebbles-grinding sound.'),
(4592, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-18', 'Love it!! So small but gets the job done!'),
(4593, 1, 1, 1, '2016-04-16', 'Would no recommend this product Shoddy product, I\'ve had two in a row have a strong plastic taste and have frequent water pressure problems. That aside, the K-Cup Monoply is real!!! The machine is fickle about when it wants to take  non K-Cups---Shoot, the machine doesn\'t even take K-Cups when it doesn\'t want to. It\'s got personality by the boatload but no functionality to speak of. Would no recommend this product, not even in a joking manner.'),
(4594, 12, 1, 2, '2015-08-12', 'Toaster not working.. only oven. Bit discouraging ... Toaster not working..only oven. Bit discouraging... and costly to return'),
(4595, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-05', 'Five Stars I am very happy with it. It is easy to use and does a good job. Henry Badger'),
(4596, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-03', 'Five Stars works perfectly'),
(4597, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'perfect coffee every time #hellokeurig keurig has done it again.  This time its a touchscreen and you can control how strong your coffee is and also decide what size cup you have!  Its so easy to use and fast!  coffee by the cup or coffee by the pot.  your choice and perfect every time.  I recieved this product for free to try to give a review.  :) @keurig @influenster'),
(4598, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-03', 'Five Stars Works like a charm and makes a great cup of coffee.  Love this product!'),
(4599, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-08', 'We use this only as a toaster and we have ... We use this only as a toaster and we have no complaints.  Works well and for the money you can\'t go wrong.'),
(4600, 8, 1, 5, '2015-12-01', 'Love it! Makes coffee, makes it fast, and measures accurately. I use it very often!'),
(4601, 8, 1, 1, '2015-02-03', 'One Star the pot is about a cup in volume'),
(4602, 5, 1, 3, '2016-06-16', 'not everything i hoped for only lasted 18 months. auto shutoff is 2 hours and buttons are loose. wont buy again :('),
(4603, 12, 1, 4, '2015-11-04', 'I like it No major problems. Tray got stained quickly and you can\'t clean it off but that is expected when cooking with grease.'),
(4604, 6, 1, 4, '2015-04-28', 'Not as awesome as I had hoped Not as awesome as I had hoped, but it is fine. Sometimes when I toast 4 pieces at once, 2 of them get overdone and I have to chuck them. Never really a rhyme or reason when it will happen. Used it last night and the 4 came out fine. Wish it was more consistent.'),
(4605, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Excellent Toaster Oven This is so the best of both worlds, I couldn\'t believe it when I found it.  It works great both as a bagel toaster and small oven.  Definitely better than a microwave for reheating pizza.  Exactly what I was looking for.  Go figure.  Amazon\'s the place!'),
(4606, 2, 1, 4, '2016-10-07', ') very good size for small :) very good size for small family.'),
(4607, 10, 1, 2, '2016-05-03', 'Bummer I had high hopes for this, but unfortunately you get what you pay for.  It leaks.  If you try to blend ice cubes they float to the top and are not sucked down by the blender.  It is a pain in the butt.  I ordered a different blender today.'),
(4608, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'Five Stars great toaster'),
(4609, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-28', '5 Stars This is a great space-saving toaster.  It works great and looks nice and high-tech.  It looks to be of very high quality and durable.  Toasted my bagels this morning very quickly.  Has a cool blue light to indicate toaster heat selections.  Highly recommended!.'),
(4610, 4, 1, 3, '2016-06-08', 'Three Stars It might work too well....'),
(4611, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-22', 'LOVE THIS COFFEE MAKER!!! Absolutely love this coffee pot!! It\'s beautiful to look at and makes a perfect cup with lots of options (keep warm temp, brew strength, etc..) 100% happy with this purchase! Update - 2/4/2015 - Only bad thing about this is that the white lettering on the buttons rubs off :/'),
(4612, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Great new model - LOVE the strong brew! I really, really like this new Keurig! I had one of the older models, but must say I\'m extremely pleased with the upgrade. My absolute FAVORITE feature is the \"strong\" brew feature. I like my coffee with a kick, and that feature certainly delivers; I found it especially better in comparison to my older Keurig\'s performance. For those who like iced coffee, I also found the strong brew feature helpful for brewing what I\'ve dubbed \"lazy iced coffee.\" I just brew a cup over ice on the strong setting and the coffee comes out really nice - it\'s iced without that watered down taste that usually accompanies a quickly brewed cup of iced. Other features I like are the various size options, the eventual option to get a Carafe, the sleek design, the touch screen display, and the quiet operation (MUCH quieter than my old one!). It really is a nice looking, well functioning machine! The only downside to this Keurig is the fact that you can only use Keurig sanctioned K-cups and that I can\'t use my \"My K-Cup\" to brew whatever I want anymore. That is definitely a bummer. I received this item for free in exchange for my thoughts and opinions. I am certainly glad I did, because it is awesome!'),
(4613, 5, 1, 1, '2016-12-16', 'Screen cover just fell off. Not a good sign.... Screen cover fell off after one day of use. Somehow the plastic pieces in there broke. Ordered a replacement but worried about quality and how long the next one will last ...'),
(4614, 9, 1, 1, '2016-01-23', 'Great for three weeks. This was a Christmas gift for my Mom, and it lasted all of three weeks. The light came on to clean the maker after three weeks. It was cleaned with vinegar and water, and never worked right again. It would only brew two cups at a time, and got so hot you couldn\'t touch it. Amazon took care of the return, but it really makes me mad they charge me $12.00 shipping on a defective item to send it back.Going to start buy electrical item locally again.'),
(4615, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-14', 'quick and easy to make good meals and not turn on the ... It\'s a must have, quick and easy to make good meals and not turn on the big oven and heating up the kitchen.'),
(4616, 5, 1, 4, '2016-08-28', 'Good for the prize. this is a pretty good product for the prize. It made out of plastic for the most part, but you don\'t get that plastic tasty in the coffee like most cheaply made coffee makers and the water faucet is removable so that is very convenient . the minute and hour buttons are a little flimsy but it gott\'s a solid feel to it.'),
(4617, 5, 1, 1, '2016-05-13', 'Overall the design and functinality WAS great. Right away though the spring seal in the ... Coffee Maker is for sure BEACHED!  Overall the design and functinality WAS great. Right away though the spring seal in the water tank just stopped working. We would have to manually push it down before filling it up with water so wather wouldn\'t leak. And just yesterday, a little over a year after we purchased it (march 2016) the mahcine just died. Plugged it in and nothing turns on. Nothing! Ugh. Our last maker, lasted 13 years, this one, 1.'),
(4618, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-08', 'Five Stars work great'),
(4619, 11, 1, 1, '2014-10-01', 'went on fire. do not buy. unsafe. ... went on fire.  do not buy.  unsafe.  asked for refund and never received.'),
(4620, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-22', 'Five Stars works great'),
(4621, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'The Best Keurig I\'ve Owned! This is definitely the best Keurig I\'ve ever owned. I love being able to brew carafes rather than a couple cups every morning. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4622, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-12', 'Highly recommend Excellent toaster.  Compact. Doesn\'t take up counter space.  Cool to touch outside compared to other toasters we have had.  Good value..'),
(4623, 10, 1, 2, '2015-05-07', 'not recommended It doesn\'t take long for this thing to start putting out an odor of burning plastic while in use. I wanted one for making smoothies, but I\'m afraid it might catch fire. I ended up getting a magic bullet for $10 more and it works well.'),
(4624, 7, 3, 2, '2016-03-13', 'slow and inconsistant when using k cups, doesnt always work with them.'),
(4625, 7, 3, 4, '2014-01-20', 'This coffeemaker met my expectiations for what I was looking for. It was 1/2 the price of a kuerig and does the exact same thing. The only shortcoming being you can only add enough water for the cup you are making at the time, and cannot have a reservoir filled for multiple cups. I am very pleased. It makes a perfect cup every time.'),
(4626, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-30', 'I make smoothies mostly. As long as there is ... I make smoothies mostly. As long as there is enough liquid it chops up ice and frozen strawberries with ease!'),
(4627, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-12', 'Five Stars excellent'),
(4628, 11, 1, 4, '2014-07-21', 'Looks great. Toasts bread. Bakes tots. Looks great.'),
(4629, 6, 1, 1, '2015-10-12', 'Horrible Unit/Horrible Customer Service We have owned many Cuisinart units in the past, including a toaster that worked great for about 10 years.  We decided to buy this one based on our past experience with Cuisinart.  Within 3 months of purchasing, the lettering next to the front buttons disintegrated.  I called Cuisinart and they said it was a \"cosmetic\" issue and was not something they were responsible for.  If this is now the quality standard for Cuisinart, I will never buy from them again.'),
(4630, 8, 1, 4, '2016-09-01', 'Good basic little pot for one person really unless you like weak coffee or less for two.  More messy to clean. This is basically a good little pot for one person only really unless you really don\'t want much coffee for two people.  The only reason I gave it four stars instead of five, is that it is a bit of a pain to clean and also did not come with a filter.  The top area where the coffee goes doesn\'t have a little bubble piece so that when the filter insert and your general filter placement area part is removed to wash it the coffee in it the grinds don\'t end up all over the pot and the bottom of the heater area and your floor.  The filter area black part has a hole that is open and goes right into the pot opening so it is messy to clean. I bought a separate filter 1-4 cup insert for this pot which works okay with it.  Works fine otherwise for a basic, simple little office coffee pot.'),
(4631, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-10', 'Broke After 2 Uses... It broke after 2 uses. TWO! 1st time was for a smoothie, 2nd time was with some cashews, onions, and potatoes. I was probably blending for about a minute or so, and then it just stopped working altogether. Wouldn\'t recommend if you\'re planning on doing anything other than smoothies with this. Even then, use sparingly.'),
(4632, 8, 1, 3, '2014-03-19', 'its okay. Its smaller so it can be quite tedious. It does do what its supposed to do. so i really didn\'t have to much expectation for it. The quality seems good so far.'),
(4633, 6, 1, 4, '2015-09-19', 'Four Stars great toaster'),
(4634, 2, 1, 3, '2016-08-05', 'Three Stars Feel like your cooking in a easy bake oven.'),
(4635, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-28', 'I don\'t recommend this. Just used this for 1st time to make almond butter... after 5 min it started smoking and the engine burned out... I don\'t recommend this.'),
(4636, 6, 1, 4, '2016-11-27', 'Four Stars it\'s fine... does what it\'s supposed to do... I\'m getting used to it.'),
(4637, 12, 1, 3, '2016-02-20', 'Oven Space Far Too Small I did not keep this product. When it arrived, I was very disappointed at how tiny the oven space is. There is not enough room for much of anything! The toaster feature/space seemed ample, although I cannot speak to functionality as I did not test it. I ended up purchasing another toaster that I love and keeping my old toaster oven by Black and Decker (still going strong fifteen years and counting) but storing it under the counter.'),
(4638, 4, 1, 4, '2016-11-07', 'Four Stars Highly efficient! Toasts and bakes very quickly!.'),
(4639, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-08', 'I really love my oven I really love my oven. I live in an RV and hated the gas oven that was in it. Threw it away and used the space for storage. Do my cooking on the counter top Black & Decker.'),
(4640, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-30', 'Five Stars Perfect for one person'),
(4641, 12, 1, 4, '2014-07-17', 'I love my little toaster I love my little toaster... I used to have a much bigger machine and it took up much space. This is a much smaller machine and does the same as my previous machine. I just have to heat up my food in smaller portions. But if I had to suggest it, I would if you don\'t have much space, the toaster part is FANTASTIC and it works and the oven part is really strong, so I have to keeps the temp low so it doesn\'t burn what I\'m heating up. I guess cause it\'s a small space the heat works fast.  All in all, it\'s a good product.'),
(4642, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-17', 'I read the review which overall seems good with several Cons being the leaking top I was looking for something to mix my smoothies/protein breakfast drink. I use frozen fruit, coconut milk (low carb) so a hand shaker with a  steel ball was not an option. I did not want to spend much either. I read the review which overall seems good with several Cons being the leaking top. I throw in my milk and fruit and blend. The first time I pulled of the top to add protein powder, they were right, It was messy. The next time I was more careful and about 60% less mess. I started pulling up one quadrant then then flip it over in one motion. The third time NO!! mess at all. I drink it out of the mixing cup and cleans up in under 2 minutes. With the blending cup and mixing tines being a single unit, no need to separate. It takes up very-very little counter space and has a nice design. And the $14.00 price just makes it even better. Great product all the way around.'),
(4643, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Satisfaction This Keurig is amazing. beautiful features. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4644, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-14', 'Four Stars Have to use care to shut door as hook to pull in rack is not secure.'),
(4645, 1, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'and I am immensely happy with the Brewer I recently purchased the K200 Keurig Brewer, and I am immensely happy with the Brewer.  I love the fact that I can brew one cup or a carafe at the touch of a finger.  The instructions were well written and easy to follow.  I love brewing my coffee without having to think about the amounts of coffee/scoops of coffee I need to add for just the right taste.  Also, I enjoy a fresh cup each time I am ready for coffee.'),
(4646, 2, 1, 2, '2015-10-28', 'Not pleased at all. I suppose you can\'t expect too much at the price, but this appliance is really annoying and not worth its trouble at any price.  It is flimsy with very thin metal.  The broiling tray is so tiny it looks and feels like a child\'s play oven.  An appliance for a doll house.  The dials are confusing, and the print on them is so tiny and badly placed that you need to set the oven on its back side to read it.  Making a slice of toast requires that you turn the timer dial clockwise past the number 10 (10 minutes, I think), then counterclockwise back to one of three tiny icons that represent slices of toast: light, medium, dark.  These are very close together on the left side of the dial, and all that twisting feels like the dial will fall off, but that is the only way to make the toaster turn off automatically.  The heating unit does heat pretty quickly, but I think it may be too quick: the toast burns on the outside without being affected inside at all.  You better like your toast very crispy, even on medium setting.  This may all work better if you are planning to bake more often than toast, but I really bought this for toasting (especially bagels, or I would have bought a slot toaster) and things like grilled cheese (which doesn\'t come out good at all).'),
(4647, 8, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Five Stars Excellent. Arrived in appropriate packagine. Product as expected.'),
(4648, 6, 1, 1, '2014-10-10', 'Faulty lever When I began to toast the first time the left lever would not stay down. Had to return the toaster. Very disappointing.'),
(4649, 9, 1, 1, '2016-08-23', 'I really wanted to love this coffeemaker I really wanted to love this coffeemaker....within one year it would brew a few cups and then stop.  Cleaned it 3 times and it just would not brew more than one or two cups despite the amount of water in the reservoir.  Ok put that aside and yes they do cover the warranty...HOWEVER!!!!  You must pay the cost of returning the old pot to AZ.  I am so disappointed in this company.'),
(4650, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-18', 'Nice little toaster for the money Nice little toaster for the money.  I use it for toast mostly as it gets the toast crisp.  Most if not all the regular toasters today leave the toast soggy in the center and if you set them to darker setting they just burn on the outside but still leave the center soggy.'),
(4651, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-06', 'Great Toaster Works Great! This one toasts the bread evenly and quickly. Very happy with the functionality of this toaster.'),
(4652, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-15', 'Works great I got this for my dad who lives alone and hates cooking big meals. He said he would rather just make food for one and use a toaster oven so this is what I bought him. He said he loves it and it works great.'),
(4653, 5, 1, 5, '2014-05-10', 'Makes great coffee Nonly is the coffee outstanding (I like the bold setting), but this appliance is easy to use and attractive.  Some have complained that it\'s impossible to pour out the last drop from the caraffe.  Not me.  This feature eliminates the annoying occurrence of many other pots of coffee sloshing out from more surfaces than the pouring spout. Moderate price, a good value.'),
(4654, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'Five Stars Love it, does what it suppose to do...'),
(4655, 5, 1, 3, '2014-12-12', 'Three Stars works ok for the money. Built cheap and takes a long time to make coffee'),
(4656, 4, 1, 1, '2015-12-22', 'Warped heating element. Same issues as others. We\'ve had this for 2 years now and one of the lower heating elements is warped pretty badly. It has been like this for awhile, and I wish I had read the reviews earlier to see this was a common problem. I thought a house sitter had put something heavy on it, but now realize it is a manufacturing issue. Time to replace.'),
(4657, 12, 1, 5, '2016-11-20', 'My favorite toaster! Love the top slot toasting option My favorite toaster!  Love the top slot toasting option.  I have had one of these in red and now just purchased this for my daughter!.'),
(4658, 5, 1, 4, '2016-07-23', 'Decent machine. Nice machine. Was hoping for an American made one like the Bunn I am replacing. Oh well, what do you expect for $40.'),
(4659, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-14', 'Great! This is my first toaster oven and I\'ve used it now for about 6 months.  It\'s great for heating up pizza or chicken nuggets, etc.  Very simple to use and the little baking tray it comes with is something I always use.  I\'ve never had any probs with this oven and I use it quite regularly.  One note is that I only paid $29 for it when I bought it so the price has gone up some.  Still, it\'s a great product.'),
(4660, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-17', 'then you will always have perfect toast. French bread pizzas fit great are come ... Not hard to figure out at all. Toasts bread for breakfast perfectly. You do need to figure out at what place you are going to set the knob for your desired toast darkness. Once you do, then you will always have perfect toast.  French bread pizzas fit great are come out perfect. Also great for toasting a ham and turkey sandwich! The timer knob is stiff, as mentioned by some reviewers, but you CAN turn it off if you are done toasting/baking. Some reviewers seem to think that because the knob is stiff, you must just let it keep running until the timer goes off, even if you are done cooking. This is not the case.  Very good little oven. Gave it 5 because for this price, you couldn\'t ask for more.'),
(4661, 7, 3, 1, '2014-09-20', 'If I still had my receipt I would return the brewer as it leaks. I followed the directions in the booklet enclosed with the brewer. It still leaked. It is sitting not being used. I will never purchase another Hamilton Beach coffee brewer of any kind. I went and purchased a Keurig Coffee Brewer. Yes it was more expensive, but it doesn\'t leak.'),
(4662, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'A great buy I adore it.'),
(4663, 1, 1, 5, '2015-11-01', 'Price was good. Received on time I was told. Price was good.'),
(4664, 8, 1, 3, '2014-04-28', 'BLACK & DECKER 5 CUP DRIP COFFE MAKER REVIEW I HAVE A SMALL KITCHEN AND WAS LOOKING FOR A NEW COFFEE MAKER THAT WAS STURDY AND FAST AND COMPACT. I HAVE KEPT THE COFFEE POT BUT WISH I HAD LOOKED AROUND A LITTLE MORE, BUT SOMETIMES ITS HARD TO SEE THE QUALITY OF A PRODUCT UNTIL YOU SEE IT. COFFEE TAKES FOREVER AND ITS SMALLER THAN I THOUGHT. AND I HATE TO SAY THIS BUT IT IS NOT THE QUALITY I WAS EXPECTING FROM BLACK & DECKER, DID NOT CONTACT SELLER AND RECD IN A TIMELY MATTER. IF OR WHEN I DECIDE TO GET A DIFFERENT COFFEE MAKER I WILL RESEARCH AT THE STORES AND COMPARE PRICES WITH AMAZON.'),
(4665, 7, 3, 2, '2016-03-30', 'I recently purchased this because my Keurig died. This makes the worst coffee I have ever had. You definitely get what you pay for. This is going back!'),
(4666, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-28', 'Five Stars Absolutely LOVE this! So convenient'),
(4667, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-15', 'Compact, efficient Does everything a toaster is supposed to do, what more can I say?'),
(4668, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-23', 'Couldn\'t be happier with this product Couldn\'t be happier with this product!  I rarely use the regular oven any more.  I use it to toast, broil and bake just about anything!'),
(4669, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-07', 'Cuisinart Toaster Looks and works as you would expect.  We don\'t use a toaster daily but this is a great replacement for our old one.  Buy it!!'),
(4670, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-24', 'My new kueirig is great First time with a single cup brewer and love it I don\'t have to waste a whole pot of coffee anymore.couldnt wait to get it'),
(4671, 6, 1, 4, '2014-12-02', 'The only thing I don\'t like about it is how I have to press the ... It\'s kind of big, but that\'s okay. It works well. The only thing I don\'t like about it is how I have to press the lever down hard (holding onto the toaster body so it doesn\'t tilt forward) in order to make it go all the way down, snap into place, and toast.'),
(4672, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-06', 'This thing is great, it is a bit time consuming to clean ... This thing is great, it is a bit time consuming to clean each morning... but the coffee is good each and every cup.'),
(4673, 2, 1, 3, '2015-06-25', 'This is not my favorite. I wanted a basic toaster oven This is not my favorite. I wanted a basic toaster oven, and didn\'t want to spend a lot, which is what I got, I suppose. Making a basic piece of toast is sort of complicated and I cannot seem to master toasting just the right amount.'),
(4674, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'Great gift! Greg price for this product. Client loved the gift!'),
(4675, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-22', 'Five Stars Good alternative to a pot'),
(4676, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'Favorite appliance. Compact in size fits my needs. Has bagel setting, removable tray easy to clean. In general operates much quicker than old toaster oven. Versatile.  I tried the Warm setting and it kept my food item warm while cooking the rest of the meal.'),
(4677, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'I\'m a Toaster, not a Cylon.... My mother in law needed a toaster, and I don\'t like wandering through Bed Bath and Beyond.  She wanted one that toasted bread, had simple controls, did not take up much room on the counter, and was not something you would find on the Starship Enterprise.  Just a simple toaster.  Not a Cylon.  Just something that toasts bread once in a while.  If that is what you need, this is it'),
(4678, 10, 1, 3, '2015-02-14', 'not good for seeds Its okay, doesn\'t blend vegetables or roughage well, not good for seeds. I like my nutribullet better.'),
(4679, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-07', 'Five Stars great'),
(4680, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-08', 'One Star Not good. Blender motor burnt out while blending ice on 2nd use.'),
(4681, 2, 1, 2, '2016-06-08', 'I Don\'t Like It I\'ve had it 9 months and the heating elements are nowhere near as hot as they were when I first got it.  It never has toasted evenly, and now an edge of the bread will burn while the rest of the slice remains untoasted.'),
(4682, 12, 1, 3, '2014-07-25', 'Three Stars Wish I got the one with timer'),
(4683, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'This is probably the best toaster I\'ve owned This is probably the best toaster I\'ve owned. The wide slice areas as perfect for thicker breads and bagels and I really like the fact that you can lift the bread higher to remove it easier. It\'s small enough to sit on the countertop without hogging space and the browning wheel is consistent in how it toasts the same breads. It was delivered when promised and packed well. I\'d buy this again and recommend it to others.'),
(4684, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'Sorry I waited so long! This has been a great product. It is the perfect size for us. Takes up only slightly larger space as our old 4-slice toaster and is a better appliance.  Easy to read controls, convenient 2-position rack, easiest-to-clean crumb drawer ever!  Toasts, bakes, broils...perfect! Love everything about this unit. As with many consumers, I hesitated to spend the $$ on this, fearing it would not be better than the less expensive varieties I had owned in the past.  As I went through my second conventional 4-slice toaster in as many years, I decided to trust the reviews and \"go for it.\"  I should have done it years ago!'),
(4685, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-07', 'Five Stars Great machine!.'),
(4686, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-09', 'Sleek and efficient for just about everything but frozen chicken tenders. This works really well and really fast for toasting bread, sandwiches, etc.  The convection function has worked well for baking cookies.  The only thing it hasn\'t worked great for is cooking raw, breaded chicken tenders.  Admittedly, we put foil under them to keep the unit clean though, so I suspect that eliminating the foil and creating more air flow would solve that problem.  Since this is probably user error on my part, it isn\'t fair to dock a star.  So, five stars it is.'),
(4687, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-23', 'Best coffee ever! This coffee maker makes the best coffee that I have ever had!'),
(4688, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', 'other than pizza it is a great toaster claimed it would do a small pizza, but it is a little too small, shipped fast, other than pizza it is a great toaster oven.'),
(4689, 4, 1, 2, '2016-11-22', 'They\'d better hope one of these things doesn\'t start a fire Bought this oven through Amazon in 2011.  Did an OK job, but after a year or so the elements started to warp and a few months later one of the elements separated and there were sparks.  We contacted Cuisinart and they ended up sending us a new replacement oven on the condition that we sent the defective oven to them.  A few months ago the elements on this replacement started to warp and it won\'t be long until one of them separates and then we will buy a replacement from another manufacturer.  Surprising that a company with Cuisinart\'s reputation would continue year after year to sell a product with this know defect.  They\'d better hope one of these things doesn\'t start a fire.'),
(4690, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-09', 'Five Stars Does the job!'),
(4691, 9, 1, 4, '2016-06-12', 'like the whole thing have had this for a couple months and we use it at our small office of 6 employees, like the whole thing, easy to use, bottom drain tray removes easily for larger cups. love the gauge to show full or empty! i\'d recommend this to anyone!'),
(4692, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-09', 'Great price, I like the crumb tray feature Great price, I like the crumb tray feature.  Toasts very evenly, best of the Black and Decker ovens I have had in the past.  I love the size, does not hog the counter, easily fits 4 slices of toast.'),
(4693, 4, 1, 1, '2015-10-08', 'Dangerous/Fire Hazard Not happy with this Cuisinart toaster oven.  A couple of weeks ago while removing English muffins from this toaster oven, one of the English muffins slipped out of my hand, landed on the open door of the Cuisinart, and slid down into the toaster oven.  The English muffin landed on the bottom heating element inside the oven and caught on fire.  I quickky unplugged the oven and determibed I didn\'t have the door fully open and that\'s why the English muffin slid into the oven.  But just today I was making toast.  I opened the door fully, reached in to get the toast.  One piece slipped through the cooking  rack and landed on the heating element and the toast caught on fire, burst into flames.  I quickky unplugged the toaster oven and carried the entire thing outside.....and that is where it will stay until garbage pickup this week.  This is dangerous oven.'),
(4694, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-27', 'Everything else is great. I just threw away a Black and Decker Toaster Oven which I had had for 10 years or more.  The toaster was set with one control which meant that when I pushed down on the on-switch, the toast always came out the same.  On this one, the on-switch is turned to the right and then let go.  I have burned quite a bit of bread.  Everything else is great.'),
(4695, 3, 1, 1, '2016-09-29', 'Funny enough, the day after this item arrived I got this countertop oven to replace my smaller toaster oven. Funny enough, the day after this item arrived, my main oven broke, so I was stuck using this for a few weeks until my regular oven was repaired. In other words, it\'s gotten a LOT of use. And so far, I haven\'t managed to successfully make much of anything. Whatever is in the back right corner of the oven ends up being burnt, and anything near the front door is barely cooked. Every pizza I\'ve tried to make has come out with burnt toppings and a soggy, raw crust. Tator tots and French fries come out raw in the middle, no matter how much you burn the outsides. Chicken tenders also come out uncooked and cold in the middle. Any kind of pasta/casserole will be burnt on top and in the back corner, but uncooked everywhere else. I\'ve tried cooking with and without the convection setting on. I\'ve tried turning up the temperature and decreasing the time. I\'ve tried turning down the temperature and increasing the time. I\'ve tried opening the door to rotate my product halfway through to make up for the uneven heating, and boy, that really ruins whatever you\'re trying to make as all the built up heat escapes out of the unit. I\'ve tried different pans. Nothing works. I thought maybe something was wrong with my unit, but if there is, I don\'t see it. All 4 heating elements appear to be working properly. I bought this unit after reading a lot of the other raving reviews, and I\'m seriously disappointed. I really regret getting rid of my small, cheap toaster oven. It worked perfectly; this doesn\'t work at all. Buy something else.'),
(4696, 5, 1, 4, '2015-09-21', 'Quality, Simple Features, Easy Setup We bought this to replace our old coffeemaker. Very pleased with the options on this model. I thought that the exterior would have real metal, but it is plastic.'),
(4697, 3, 1, 4, '2015-02-24', 'Great oven We really like this oven. Easy to work and clean. The only disappointment is that one of the slats on the wire rack broke while washing it.'),
(4698, 6, 1, 3, '2014-10-01', 'Three Stars it doesn\'t have a very dark setting even though it thinks that it does'),
(4699, 11, 1, 4, '2014-06-10', 'Black & Decker Roaster Overn I love size and it is very easy to use. Just two of us and just right size for us.'),
(4700, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-05', 'The coffee maker came with a small basket for ground coffee which is a surprise to me. I have mad coffee most days. Taste is good. Easy to use and clean. Love it!'),
(4701, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-01', 'Bow down to your God I love this thing. There is nothing more I could possibly say. Coffee is life, and Keurig is the provider of my life force. All praise the maker of delicious smelling, hot coffee, caffeine provider of our lives!'),
(4702, 1, 1, 1, '2016-08-23', 'Defective after 2 uses. Coffee is full of grounds ... Defective after 2 uses.  Coffee is full of grounds, the K-cup and area under the lid were covered with grounds and water.  I contacted Keurig and they suggested I clean and descale it... after two uses!.'),
(4703, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-21', 'It preheats quickly and cooks perfectly. Had another brand ... It preheats quickly and cooks perfectly.  Had another brand which was junk but this is high quality and can handle 9x13 pans.'),
(4704, 12, 1, 4, '2015-09-08', 'we had one exactly like this before and so I got another one on ... we had one exactly like this before and so I got another one on Prime Day and we really do like the the toaster feature for making pizza toast, etc'),
(4705, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-13', 'perfect for small spaces and looks really nice This toaster oven is great for what it is. We needed a small, inexpensive oven to fit into a very small space, so this fit the bill just right. Can it hold an entire round frozen pizza? NO! But if it could, it wouldn\'t fir into our allotted space. But it also looks nice, and heats the food evenly and perfectly.'),
(4706, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Five Stars You get what you pay for!!'),
(4707, 7, 3, 5, '2014-08-14', 'Love this coffee maker. The price was low and it performs like a more expensive brewer. The only suggestion I can make, I like a really hot cup of coffee and I run one cup of plain water through the machine and then make my coffee. The first run is hot but not hot enough for me. No complaints, this flexbrew is a winner!'),
(4708, 1, 1, 1, '2016-05-21', 'Squeeze the addict -Thanks Keurig but NO thanks It seems to me that having gotten folks habituated, addicted really, to Columbian coffee, Keurig is trying to squeeze every last drop of profits from us. Not sure its legal but definitely immoral. I will be finding alternatives EVEN IF I HAVE TO FLY TO COLUMBIA TO DO SO.'),
(4709, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-08', 'Five Stars Great toaster oven at an affordable price. Beats the other more expensive brands.'),
(4710, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-24', 'This is one serious value for your kitchen. Oh yes. Toast, Bake, Broil. Timer or the always-on. Keep-warm to full broil. For $20 this Black & Decker is hard to beat. Comes with rack and little pan. Cover either with foil and you\'ll barely even need to clean it. So versatile. Such a great value. Not a large oven, but you knew that, right? If I was stuck on a desert island, I\'d want this toaster and an outlet. One could probably even figure out a way to desalinize water using the coils... but I digress. If you came here looking for cheap but solid toaster, found one you have.'),
(4711, 5, 1, 1, '2015-03-19', 'Didn\'t last a year! Within a year of receiving this coffeemaker, it is no longer working. The heating element quit working and it will not brew coffee. It was only used for 8 1/2 months and in a 2 person household. I did really like the Model 46201 as being able to remove the water container for filling was very convenient. It also pivoted on the counter easily. The carafe did dribble as so many do, but all in all the size and ease of use was very positive. But the fact that it did not last for even a year erased all the good things that I could say about this machine.'),
(4712, 8, 1, 5, '2015-01-13', 'Five Stars Great price and product'),
(4713, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-05', 'Good space saving toaster. Good toaster. The extra push-up lever for small items is especially helpful for grabbing things out of it. Nice, even toasting. So much better than the one we had for $14 before. The settings are accurate and everything toasts at the correct level.'),
(4714, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-21', 'toaster oven I bought this for my sister and she loves it. I would recommend it'),
(4715, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'Five Stars Nice design and quality. Toasts well!.'),
(4716, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-05', 'Great Coffee Maker We replaced a Cuisinart machine that cost more and leaked. We\'ve had this a few months and so far, we\'re very pleased. It makes good coffee, and putting the water in the machine is a lot easier than with our Cuisinart. It\'s a good machine, especially for the price.'),
(4717, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Love my new Keurig! I\'ve never had my own Keurig before and I was very glad to get this one. It is very easy to use and I love the fact that it is so simple. No more waiting for the old school coffee makers to brew my coffee! I also love all the different types of K-cups you can use and the fact that you can make your coffee be as strong as you would like for it to be. I also like the touch screen feature that now comes with this newer addition of the Keurig line. All of these things provide the perfect user friendly experience! **I received this product free for testing.'),
(4718, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-28', '... coffee makers and this one is by far my favorite. It even makes maxwell house taste good I own 9 other coffee makers and this one is by far my favorite. It even makes maxwell house taste good. It takes a while to brew a full pot on bold setting. I think it took around 15 minutes to brew a pot. But the coffee tastes great. I am yet to fiddle with the hotplate settings as I brew enough coffee to fill my thermos. It is highly recommended.'),
(4719, 5, 1, 2, '2014-04-10', 'Not worth it Before this coffeemaker, I had a $3 coffeemate that I bought from a Target on a Black Friday.  And yet, I can\'t say for sure that this Hamilton Beach coffeemaker is any better. Cons: - coffee doesn\'t fully pour out of the spout because there is an inner lip.  This is stupid and annoying. - no-drip feature doesn\'t work, even once the coffee has stopped.  A drop falls about half the time. - A bit cheap looking. Pros: - \"Bold\" setting - multiple heat settings (although I always just use the hottest) - out-swinging coffee filter tray. - removable water container Overall, I\'d recommend something else.'),
(4720, 3, 1, 1, '2016-02-11', 'Fire hazard due to tray below heating elements Unfortunately, this oven has a seriously flawed design. Buyer beware.  Someone else has reviewed about the same problem but I will state it again: I\'ve had this oven since August, kept good care of it, cleaning it often.  However, there is a metal tray or \"trough\" below the heating element,  which is not removable and therefore impossible to clean. This tray accumulates crumbs, grease, fat, etc., and the unit is now smoking each time I use it. It\'s become a fire hazard and unusable. It\'s such a silly flawed design, I\'m surprised the company has not realized it. See photo for example of dirty tray, and clean tray.'),
(4721, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-08', 'Four Stars Good for it\'s price. It does the job.'),
(4722, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-28', 'Five Stars It\'s a good easy to use toaster oven'),
(4723, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-02', 'other than every product I\'ve owned in great quality. what can I say about cuisinart? other than every product I\'ve owned in great quality.'),
(4724, 11, 1, 1, '2014-01-31', 'Worst one on the market Horrible toaster oven. The toast will burn in one minute. I am going to throw it in the trash and go to a store and buy another.'),
(4725, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-15', 'One year old and still going strong! I got this blender last year for Christmas.  I have used it almost everyday since then and it works great!  It is important to cut fruit up a bit add liquid first, and pulse the blender if you have large pieces or ice in it. This prevents overheating of the motor.  A great little blender for smoothies!'),
(4726, 12, 1, 1, '2017-01-09', 'One Star Nope! Burned stuff! Had to return it!.'),
(4727, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Great Product Love it!!! It travels well and is powerful for its size. Glad I bought it.'),
(4728, 12, 1, 5, '2015-09-11', 'Five Stars perfect size, toaster works beautiful same as the oven'),
(4729, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-22', 'How could I have missed something so great? Never owned a toaster oven before. How could I have missed something so great?  Use this oven almost every day. Purchased because I live in Nevada. When its over 110 degrees and I want a steak or a hamburger or meatloaf or grilled fish, without using my big, hot full sized oven, this baby does the job.  It holds 4 English muffin halves or two over-sized bagel halves. It fits easily on most counter tops and has an excellent three prong plug which is very well insulated and does not spark when you unplug it.  Never experienced any unpleasant odor, smoking of  the unit or difficulty with the rack not sliding in and out easily. I saw these comments in some of the reviews but ordered anyway as most of the reviews were positive. After just over a month of use, it is easy to understand why this is the #1 best seller in toaster ovens, and it\'s not just the price.'),
(4730, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-06', 'Five Stars Great roster, work well'),
(4731, 8, 1, 4, '2016-01-12', 'Makes great coffee, same as a Mr Makes great coffee, same as a Mr. Coffee but with 5 cups instead of 4. Mr. Coffee makes a 5 cup, but only in white. There is no shut-off valve at the bottom of the strainer, so if you pull out the coffee pot before the brewing cycle is complete, the strainer will continue to pour out onto the hot plate. Not a big deal to us, but someone used to the Mr Coffee brand will notice that difference at some point.'),
(4732, 6, 1, 1, '2015-11-28', 'Stopped working in less than 1 year We used this toaster 4 - 5 days a week for almost a year. Eventually, the lever and the heating element stopped working.'),
(4733, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-14', 'Five Stars Love it. Looks great on counter, toasts perfectly.'),
(4734, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-16', 'love it, ill never have to use my oven Made a pizza as soon as we got it set up! It fits the HEB self rising pizza perfectly! love it, ill never have to use my oven again'),
(4735, 6, 1, 2, '2016-10-07', 'Great looking - lots of features Cons Pros: Great looking - lots of features Cons: Not very compact.  Biggest issue was uneven toasting no matter the darkness setting (had to return).'),
(4736, 12, 1, 2, '2014-09-06', 'Two Stars It was okay but not able to do what I bought it for so I returned it.'),
(4737, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'love it Love that you don\'t have to pull the coffer maker out from under the cabinet to fill the water or coffee...also easy to set clock and auto start'),
(4738, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Good product Great no problems.'),
(4739, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-06', 'Five Stars Love my new toaster oven'),
(4740, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-03', 'Five Stars Very nice all around product. Good price.'),
(4741, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Five Stars Really nice. Had one previous same brand and make love both of them.'),
(4742, 4, 1, 3, '2015-12-13', 'Expected More from a Cuisinart Love the space inside! Just heated leftover apple pie and put the full-size aluminum pie pan in it. Love the interior design. Simple two row-design with the ability to flip the rack and make two additional levels. Like the different options -- bagel, toast, bake, warm, etc. My issues are with the cooking consistency. First, the 3rd knob with the light to dark gauge doesn\'t have specific levels (would\'ve lot rather had 10 clicks) so you have to guesstimate how far between the two marks was the right level of darkness. 2nd, the two bars of heating elements going across the bottom (and I assume the top) do not heat evenly. I figured out that if I center my food over one of the heating elements it cooks fine, but if you put something right in the center of the oven, it won\'t be toasted as much in the center of the oven as directly over an element. 3rd, cooking is not consistent. One day, my toast will be toasted perfectly on a certain darkness setting; the next day on exactly the same setting, it will be barely warmed. It doesn\'t change radically; it\'s adequate, but I expected more from a Cuisinart.'),
(4743, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'Best product for your dollar! I have had mine for five years!!! It finally went sour on me this morning. it still works, but not for what I need. I make shakes daily, with kale, or bananas, other fruits, yogurt, seeds, peanut butter, etc. It never gave me problems. I had just washed it and think maybe there was too much moisture around the base, when I turned it on too blend it started smoking and the motor was very sluggish. After 5 years, and over 1,000 shakes later, I am desperate to go out and buy a new one! I  just hope this next one I have, has the same manufacturing quality and last me long. For the price even a year is a Five-Star product. I refuse to try a different type knowing this one was so excellent!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(4744, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-04', 'I love everything about this coffee pot I love everything about this coffee pot!  It is far superior to other coffee makers I have owned.  I especially like having the choice to make the brew BOLD!'),
(4745, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-12', 'Simple, reliable, easy to clean, makes good coffee We replaced another model from this same manufacturer, mostly because my coffee cup didn\'t fit under the fill spout. Well, this one works just as well (if not better) than the one we replaced. Seems to make consistent brews, and it gets the water hot enough to make good coffee. It\'s pretty much everything you\'d want from a basic coffee maker: simple, reliable, easy to clean, makes good coffee.'),
(4746, 9, 1, 1, '2016-11-11', 'definitely would not buy this again.  The Charcoal filter is nice. This coffee maker leaks water every time I use it.  The Gauge on the front doesn\'t work.  And I can\'t fit taller coffee cups in it.'),
(4747, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-10', 'Four Stars I like it except that the door doesn\'t pull out the rack when you open it.'),
(4748, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-09', 'Mona. Pa I love it! It makes great toast and great toasted bagels!'),
(4749, 6, 1, 2, '2015-05-03', 'Useless \"bagel\" button.  Uneven toasting. I bought this toaster because of the good reviews, but I am returning it.  On every toaster I ever used, the \"bagel\" function toasts one side only.  On the Cuisinart toaster, it adds \"extra time\"  to compensate for the thickness, and toasts (or burns)  both sides.  Who needs that?  ,Also, it toasted  unevenly.  Looks like many buyers didn\'t have this problem, but we did.  Very disappointing.'),
(4750, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-21', 'Great product! We use this almost everyday. Great product!'),
(4751, 8, 1, 5, '2015-11-15', 'Five Stars nice product,a dn reliable'),
(4752, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-25', 'Four Stars WORKS FINE'),
(4753, 8, 1, 3, '2016-01-13', 'Flawed design, but inexpensive. This is a review of the B&D DCM600B 5-Cup Coffeemaker. This is an inexpensive unit purchased as a giveaway until my own coffeemaker coincidentally broke that same week. After using it for a few weeks, I can only give it three stars. Main problem is that there\'s no brew interrupt. I.e., you cannot remove the carafe until the coffee is completely brewed. If you do then coffee spills onto the hotplate. Once the brewing seems to cease, there\'s still a good amount of coffee pouring down and unless one checks by peeking through the 1/4\" gap to spot black coffee against the black plastic. coffee will spill. And that\'s a tragic. For a hotel room or as a backup coffeemaker this is adequate. As a daily brewer it\'s not.'),
(4754, 8, 1, 1, '2016-01-30', 'Expected life: 6 months This product only \"worked\" for 6 months before it stopped working altogether. During that time it was nearly impossible to pour from the carafe without making a mess. You also cannot remove the carafe during brewing. I would never buy one of these again.'),
(4755, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-12', 'Quite  pleased Love this Keurig because of the ability to make a pot of coffee when  I have company. Only concern is that water has to be added  more frequently than my last Keurig.'),
(4756, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-08', 'Best simple coffee maker This is the pinnacle of simple drip coffee maker innovation and engineering. Please never discontinue this model, for the sake of humankind. The removable water container and front pop-out grinds loader make this so much more pleasant to use.'),
(4757, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-07', 'Such a great blender, Always have 2 in my house since ... Such a great blender , Always have 2 in my house since it is priced so gosh darn well'),
(4758, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-29', 'I haven\'t had the best of luck with coffee makers Recently, I haven\'t had the best of luck with coffee makers.  This is a welcomed change!  It\'s easy-to-use and makes great-tasting coffee.'),
(4759, 10, 1, 2, '2015-12-04', 'Started out good, but no longer works At first I really, really liked this blender. It is straight-forward,easy to use, and makes perfect portions. But after using it a few times, it is like the blades went dull or something. It will no longer blend anything frozen, or anything that is too mushy. I have to chop everything up in my food processor to get it nice and chopped, prior to using the blender. I would recommend getting one that is a little better quality.'),
(4760, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-28', ') level is really nice; no more tipping the toaster This toaster works fast, the darkness of the toast per the regulator is right on the mark, and the feature for holding the toast at a grabbable (is that a word?) level is really nice; no more tipping the toaster, or unplugging it and sticking a fork in to pull the toast out like we had to do with our old toaster.  It\'s also a reasonable size, so doesn\'t use up excessive counter space. I\'m really happy with this purchase!'),
(4761, 2, 1, 3, '2016-02-28', 'First toaster I got was so dented that the door ... First toaster I got was so dented that the door couldn\'t even close. Lucky for the free returns, I got a replacement one in a couple of days. The dial is a little hard to dial in perfectly as not to burn your toast.'),
(4762, 2, 1, 1, '2015-08-31', 'One Star Oven doesn\'t heat up fast and doesn\'t stay at a consistent temp. Also difficult to clean.'),
(4763, 8, 1, 5, '2014-02-04', 'Great Value Works great , makes a nice pot of coffee just needed something inexpensive for when the relatives visit...I\'m an Irish Breakfast tea man myself. Great Buy'),
(4764, 5, 1, 2, '2016-06-14', 'Lasted 6 Months. Well, I was just getting ready to post a positive review after having this coffee maker since December 2015, but the coffee maker just died.  :  I just walked in to the kitchen to make lunch and noticed the coffee pot\'s screen was off.  I checked the power cord, just to make sure it didn\'t come loose -- nope.  I swapped it with the coffee bean grinder which is on the same outlet and working fine -- no change. It\'s not just the screen either -- the pot won\'t turn on at all.  So this thing has barely lasted 6 months, being used once per day for morning coffee.  The carafe is great and doesn\'t spill and it brews quickly, but it\'s the shortest-lived coffee pot I\'ve ever owned. I guess I have to contact the manufacturer now?  Yay, that\'s always fun.  I\'ll post a follow-up after going through the warranty process. *** UPDATE #1 6/14/2016 *** I spoke with Hamilton Beach customer service.  They answered right away, no hold-time.  I was asked to pay an $11.40 shipping fee for a replacement coffee maker, which isn\'t too bad.  I was told it will be 10-14 days before it arrives, so I guess no coffee for the next two weeks.  :D I guess I\'m sort of torn.  This is the shortest-lived coffee maker I\'ve ever owned.  Sure, mechanical devices fail, I get it, but this was pretty damn quick to fail.  I\'m pleased that Hamilton Beach is replacing it with simply my word that it\'s broken, although they did require me to cut the power cord and email them a picture before they\'d agree to ship me a replacement, which I get. So all in all, they made the replacement process easy, but it stinks that I\'ll be without coffee for two weeks.  : I\'ll try to post a status update again next year, if this one lasts longer than 6 months.  I will likely not be purchasing another Hamilton Beach coffee maker though, come-time to do so.'),
(4765, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-05', 'Absolutely love this brew station coffee maker Absolutely love this brew station coffee maker. I\'ve had them all and this one is well built, and easy to read all gauges.'),
(4766, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-16', 'I looked everywhere for the right coffee maker when I found this one! My husband loves it. It makes the one cup of coffee so there is none to throw away. What\'s good about it is you can use pods, your regular coffee or you can put containers of coffee in there. We have told several people about this coffee maker and I know of 2 of our friends went and bought the same one and they love it also!!!'),
(4767, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Just purchased the Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve coffee maker and it worked flawlessly. I haven\'t experienced any of the complaints listed in previous reviews and you can\'t beat the price as compared to other name brand single serve coffee makers. Would recommend.'),
(4768, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-06', 'The little toaster oven. Just what I wanted.'),
(4769, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-03', 'Great toaster, easy to operate as well as clean Great toaster, easy to operate as well as clean.  Your toast doesnt fly acrossed the room when pops up either.'),
(4770, 12, 1, 1, '2015-05-09', 'We owned the same toaster for 9 years. Bought ... We owned the same toaster for 9 years.  Bought a new one and the toaster part died after a month.  Two days after I could return it to Amazon :('),
(4771, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-06', 'Five Stars It works as expected.'),
(4772, 6, 1, 1, '2015-08-26', 'Fine for the first few weeks, then awful. Same old junky toaster that most of the companies are selling these days - $30 and 6 months after purchase, one slot toasts only one side of the toast and the other burns the top part of the toast before it toasts the rest of the bread.'),
(4773, 4, 1, 4, '2017-01-23', 'the last one lasted 4 years of 2x a day use-it\'s a good deal. Second one we\'ve owned. the last one lasted 4  years of 2x a day use-it\'s a good deal.'),
(4774, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'seems just as nice as much pricier upscale names we\'ve owned before well designed, seems just as nice as much pricier upscale names we\'ve owned before, compact flat face, takes up a minimum of room, easiest water reservoir to refill, same for filters- simply swings open no snaps, catches, superfluous doodads to break or get in the way. quality of some other hamilton beach products are so-so, somewhat pedestrian, but this one had been great - solid, hassle free'),
(4775, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-17', 'Five Stars Fantastic!'),
(4776, 8, 1, 1, '2015-04-04', 'NO automatic shut off Just before  starting a month-long hospital stay, I ordered a new 5 cup Black & Decker coffeemaker to replace the same model (so I thought) Black & Decker 5 cup Black & Decker coffeemaker which I have owned and loved for many years. Turns out though the new model does NOT have an automatic shut off--it stays on and on and on, until I presume something very bad (which I do not care to learn what) happens.  This makes it useless for me.  And I\'m over the thirty day return policy, so I guess my only option at this point is to contact the Consumer Product Safety Commission.'),
(4777, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'Five Stars was a great buy, would buy from this seller again.'),
(4778, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-19', 'Keurig is amazing! I have been a lover of keurig for quite a few years now and I love this one too! I really like being able to make a single cup of coffee whenever I want and different kinds.  Also no coffee goes to waste this way!  I am loving the new space saving design of the water container as well! I got this keurig for free for testing purposes.'),
(4779, 2, 1, 3, '2016-03-30', 'Great toaster for $23 Great toaster for $23!!! I\'ve had others that were much more expensive and this is just as good so far.'),
(4780, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-29', 'Good little toaster... Had to play with browning dial for different types of breads but once this was done...works great!  Love that it has the lever to pull up on to get bread out...'),
(4781, 7, 3, 3, '2015-12-01', 'It is most convenient to have three different types of brew in one and I use all of them, sometimes in one single morning. I have pods by Wolfgang, Sumatra in regular drip and a variety of K-cups. I only wish that this machine wasn\'t made of all plastic parts. It feels flimsy and not as sturdy as my other machines. My kitchen counter is definitely neater and cleaner.'),
(4782, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-06', 'Five Stars Excellent personal blender'),
(4783, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-23', 'Five Stars Great Coffee Maker!'),
(4784, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'Great Toaster Oven This toaster oven is great.  I warm food in it everyday instead of using a microwave.  10 minutes on 350 and I have perfectly warmed food. It is easy to keep clean too.'),
(4785, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-23', 'The removable reservoir is easy and convenient to remove and fill I received this unit yesterday and brewed my first cup of coffee this morning and was thoroughly impressed. The removable reservoir is easy and convenient to remove and fill. Filter, coffee grounds, and water went in like a breeze.The navigation in setting up the auto-brew feature was simple and quick and woke up this morning to my favorite morning smell. For the price, quality, and features of this unit it was well worth the $43 I spent on it. Bottom line, it does what it should do and pretty well I might add!'),
(4786, 2, 1, 3, '2015-05-12', 'Three Stars Direction dials are labeled in tiny letters'),
(4787, 7, 3, 2, '2016-12-03', 'takes too long to brew and is not sufficiently hot.'),
(4788, 11, 1, 3, '2014-08-21', 'Not perfect, but can\'t complain for the price We don\'t use this for anything other than toast... it has taken some getting used to. The toast setting is way too powerful and burns your toast in minutes. You just have to ignore the guidance markers. The tray that it comes with blocks the heat from the bottom, so only one side of the toast is toasted. Overall, it does an okay job of toasting, is convenient for doing a toasty or cheese melt and it has a small footprint size. For $25, i can\'t complain! If you can spare the counter space compared to conventional toaster, i would recommend this.'),
(4789, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-03', 'Great toaster and compact Great toaster and compact. I like the features it has and the extra tray inside. It heats up pretty fast and cooks well. I love using this toaster especially when cooking something small and not having to heat up the oven. I have this in the kitchen counter and it doesn\'t take much space.'),
(4790, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-24', 'One Star I will stick with the old fashioned way of making coffee'),
(4791, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-29', 'Five Stars yup. it makes coffee'),
(4792, 11, 1, 3, '2014-08-25', 'This is a good toaster oven for the price This is a good toaster oven for the price.  The control knobs knobs are different than any oven I\'ve ever had and took some getting used to.'),
(4793, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-07', 'Great with some great features Great with some great features. I agree with the previous positive reviews.  Keeps the coffee really hot.  I like the removable water tank and different adjustments available. The only downside is no big deal for me. The lip on the carafe lid won\'t allow ALL of the liquid to be poured out easily. A tablespoon worth still remains.  I would buy it again. Well, a year later and my original review still stands. It does not drip, keeps the coffee HOT not warm and I really have come to love the \"Bold Brew\" option. Someone asked me about the wattage...900Watts. One more good thing. It took some teenager abuse while I was away on deployment. It still looks and works great.'),
(4794, 6, 1, 1, '2016-04-19', 'Defective This particular one had to be defective.  It burned toast and bagels on the lowest setting.  You had to constantly watch the toaster and manually pop up the toast to prevent burning.  We returned it.'),
(4795, 5, 1, 1, '2015-09-03', 'One Star Terrible, broke after 30 days & couldn\'t return. What a joke'),
