(4798, 11, 1, 3, '2015-07-06', 'So-So Oven Nothing special...I\'m famous for burning toast!'),
(4799, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-02', 'This looks so good in my white kitchen This looks so good in my white kitchen!  Works great!  It\'s compact but brews up to 10 oz at a time.  It also does the carafe (which i never use).'),
(4800, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-13', 'A good coffe maker, It works very well, it does not spill while pouring. easy to setup and use. Very attractive and looks great.'),
(4801, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-04', 'Four Stars Just what we needed!!.'),
(4802, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-07', 'I can\'t say enough good things about this toaster My Krups toaster had been on its last legs for over a year now, taking up to five minutes to simply toast a bagel. I finally decided to pull the trigger and purchased this basic Cuisinart model. What the heck was I waiting for?! Wow, does this thing toast fast! There are four presets, one of which includes \"bagel.\" Even without reading the book and figuring out the specific settings, I set the temperature dial between 3-4. Et voil! I was actually shocked how quickly and perfectly this new toaster toasted my bagel. I immediately packaged up my old toaster and swiftly threw it in the trash. I can\'t say enough good things about this toaster. For someone who needs to get ready quickly in the morning or is simply starving and doesn\'t feel like waiting around, this toaster is perfection. For everyone else who doesn\'t enjoy waiting around while their old toaster takes as long as and an Easy Bake Oven (a joke often made about my old toaster), this is the toaster for you!'),
(4803, 3, 1, 3, '2014-08-08', 'A good basic unit A good basic unit, it gets the job done very effectively. The features offered at this price are very good. I bought another model first with the dials you turn to set the temperature, time, etc. and returned it as it was not very precise. The controls offered on this countertop oven let you set the temp and time as in a full size oven.'),
(4804, 8, 1, 5, '2014-08-23', 'Five Stars It is really a good one.'),
(4805, 8, 1, 5, '2014-06-28', 'Perfect for a single person who likes to brew one cup of coffee at a time It is the perfect size for a single person.  It takes up very little counter space.  I make one cup of coffee at a time.'),
(4806, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-28', 'I have had a Black & Decker for years and when I decided to downsize this unit was a perfect fit. The only thing I don\'t like ve I have been very please with this Toaster Oven.  I have had a Black & Decker for years and when I decided to downsize this unit was a perfect fit.  The only thing I don\'t like versus the older one is you could move the rack lower or higher on the old one and you can\'t with this.  Other than that, it\'s perfect.'),
(4807, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-14', 'Good, basic, toaster oven I purchased this toaster oven as a replacement for one is my vacation rental property.  It toasts well and has good coverage.  It is small, so if you are wanting to cook a pizza or something big, this is not the option for you.  I actually like the small footprint, as the kitchen in my rental property is small.  All in all, a good, inexpensive, basic toaster oven.'),
(4808, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-26', 'Five Stars very good_'),
(4809, 7, 3, 5, '2016-12-18', 'I got this for my daughter as a birthday gift. She loves it.'),
(4810, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'Love the 2.0 I bought the original Keurig when they first came out. I then passed it on to my parents and upgraded to the 2.0. I love it! It\'s so great having the option to select so many different sizes and to indicate if the Kcup isn\'t for coffee but instead cocoa or other specialty drinks. It makes a difference! The option for making a full carafe of coffee is very appealing as well! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(4811, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-24', 'I Recommend It I use this coffee maker on a daily basis, and I adore it! I had to purchase it when my old coffee maker finally broke down. I like being able to adjust the temperature setting. It is easy-to-use and brews pretty well. If you\'re on a budget and cannot afford something more complex and fancy, I recommend the Hamilton Beach 12-Cup Digital Coffee Maker. I\'ve had mine for months now with no regrets!'),
(4812, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-08', 'It works fine, very straight forward This replaced an older model. It works fine, very straight forward. Not fancy. Does what I need. Only complaint is that the bottom doesn\'t open for cleaning like the old one. There is a crumb tray.'),
(4813, 5, 1, 3, '2015-10-17', 'Three Stars Coffee maker was great - we loved it until it just stopped working...after only 9 months.'),
(4814, 3, 1, 2, '2016-05-26', 'Difficult for older eyes to read the buttons It\'s very difficult for older eyes to read the buttons - I have to return it.  :(  The labels look very clear here online when enlarged, but in reality, there\'s not enough contrast for my 90 year old FIL. It looks very nice on the counter. It does have a crumb tray - in response to a few reviews that say it doesn\'t. It does.'),
(4815, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-19', 'I want to start by saying this is one Fantastic Coffee Maker I want to start by saying this is one Fantastic Coffee Maker.As long as i have had this Not 1 bit of trouble at all.I must say tho sometimes all the steps needed to make a great cup of coffee is a little much that early in the morning.I buy roasted coffee beans to use in this maker so thats a few added steps.Fresh Roasted Beans/Fresh Ground are the Best, so if you are using store bought ground coffee your really missing out on a Great cup of Coffee.On to the Review-- This Maker is Fast--makes Hot Coffee--Keeps it Hot for awhile too.Some other reviews Ive seen said it leaks water/coffee--not the case here with mine.Cleaning is some what of a task tho(coffee basket,gold coffee filter,coffee reservoir).Keep it clean for that Perfect Cup.All in All I really enjoy this Maker.'),
(4816, 12, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'Meets my needs perfectly I had one and loved it. I saw that a new model had come out and tried it and did not like it.  I returned it and bought this one that is the same as the one I had - still love it.'),
(4817, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-29', 'I\'m glad to have the option of brewing into the karate Brews well, I\'m glad to have the option of brewing into the karate. Bummer that the water tank is small.'),
(4818, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-07', 'The Best Toaster oven !! This is my first toaster oven , I love it, perfect for cooking in the summer , the kitchen does get hot anymore,and it is easy to keep clean and the food is cooked to perfection!!!'),
(4819, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-18', 'Way better then a Microwave This is a extra large oven and fits big pizzas pretty good. We have used this product for months now and heats up very fast and works phenominal. Way better then microwave radiation. Seriouly'),
(4820, 11, 1, 1, '2015-03-17', 'I don\'t recommend this product We purchased this item on June 7, 2014. I noticed it wasn\'t working well in December. But now it doesn\'t cook the food at all. I had quiches in there for 15 minutes at 450 degrees and they were barely warmed. I don\'t recommend this product.'),
(4821, 4, 1, 4, '2016-12-14', 'Only bummer is that when the wire rack and tray get too dirty to clean well Works well enough. Small footprint a major plus in our 90 year old home with smaller than typical counter sizes. Only bummer is that when the wire rack and tray get too dirty to clean well, the replacements add up to almost the cost of the unit itself. Seems wasteful. I think most toasters are hard to clean, or maybe I just use it so much that without being super diligent, it\'s difficult.'),
(4822, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-27', 'Nice oven Purchased for my friend, who says it works great! Can cook 2 small pizzas!'),
(4823, 7, 3, 1, '2016-07-31', 'Within a month to six weeks, it had trouble brewing. I spent my time trying to unclog the needle. I don\'t mind a monthly cleaning, but every day I had to clean it, sometimes more than once. I had already destroyed the box or back to Walmart it would have gone. I bought in December and it died permanently in July. To send it back for warranty repair, the buyer pays for shipping. Essentially, we are asked to throw good money after bad. I threw the unit in the garbage and bought a Cuisinart.'),
(4824, 1, 1, 3, '2015-09-09', 'Works fine, but takes a long time to \"preheat\" for ... Works fine, but takes a long time to \"preheat\" for each cup.  Also, water seems to spill out from top when brewing a pot.'),
(4825, 3, 1, 5, '2014-07-21', 'Great Little Toaster Oven This toaster oven is everything that I hoped it would be.  We have had it for about a month and we mainly use it for reheating leftovers and toasting bread and bagels.  I is very attractive with a streamlined appearance and it fits easily on our kitchen counter.  The sides door and top do get hot so it is good to be cautious when using.  We just use a potholder and have not had a problem.  It will easily fit a frozen 12\" pizza.  I comes with a rack, a tray and a broiling tray.  We haven\'t used it as a substitute for or large oven to cook a meal because we did\'t really buy it for that purpose.'),
(4826, 2, 1, 2, '2016-01-26', 'I HATE THIS TOASTER SO MUCH I HATE THIS TOASTER SO MUCH! I\'m selling it and spending more $$ to buy a new one. Completely baffled how it is a best seller - I have never had so many complaints about a highly rated product. Pros: Doesn\'t take up as much counter space as some of the big ones and still fits 4 Eggo waffles in it - it is fairly deep The oven part works nicely and cooks evenly. I\'ve mostly only used it to heat up pizza and pastries and it makes the crusts crisp, which is nice CONS: The thing I HATE the most that is prompting my return is: NO TOAST SETTING that stays put!! Most toasters have a slide or something that you can move from light to dark. You figure out where you like it and you leave it there. This does not have this. It has a stupid knob that you turn on every single time to toast and you have to figure out where it goes on the short little dial to make it like you like it. NO consistency.  I NEVER get it right and if you walk away (which I always do), most of the time I end up burning it and throwing it in the trash and starting over and trying to remember to stand there. It\'s also pretty slow to toast. 2 - You have to move around 3 different dials/settings to turn on the oven part. You switch the bottom one to \"stay on\", the middle dial to \"bake\" and the top one to a temperature. When you\'re done, you have to remember to turn all 3 dials back to toast if that\'s how you mainly use it. I hate it so much.'),
(4827, 4, 1, 3, '2015-05-06', 'Only lasts 16months We loved this item until a few weeks ago. We\'ve had this oven less than a year and a half. It worked great and then just up and quit without any problems. If you want something that\'s going to last then don\'t buy this product. If you only want it to work for a year then this is your oven.'),
(4828, 10, 1, 2, '2016-03-04', 'It was great for the first few days It was great for the first few days, but its very hard to clean. I noticed mold growing around the thing that holds the blade. Not worth the purchase! I wish they sold the cups by themselves to replace mine.'),
(4829, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-03', 'Five Stars Good Buy, Working as described...'),
(4830, 8, 1, 5, '2015-02-04', 'Great little coffee maker Great little coffee maker, just what I was looking for to downgrade from my 12 cup.  Makes great coffee without all the frills!'),
(4831, 12, 1, 5, '2015-03-09', 'A really good little appliance. Glad we got it. This is a great product. It looks good. It actually functions as a regular toaster or, with the flip of a switch, a toaster oven. It does both very well, and so saves space. And cheap at the price. It\'s super.'),
(4832, 10, 1, 1, '2016-01-13', 'The worst! I\'ve this owned this thing for over a year and it\'s the worst. It had a hard time crushing anything. Even frozen fruit. The engine overheats and will smoke. I have to shake it while it\'s blending just to make sure it gets everything. I\'m online now looking to replace this thing.'),
(4833, 7, 3, 5, '2016-03-05', 'I\'ve had this for a couple of weeks now and it is awesome. My keurig didn\'t even hold up a week.'),
(4834, 2, 1, 3, '2016-05-13', 'Three Stars A little more than I wanted. Fancy, but for the price I am thrilled'),
(4835, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'perfection in a cup I already loved keurig. But this one is amazing. I love the screen. The fact that there are multiple brewing options. And the look... Well not to sound lame but cool. Very modern. I\'m so glad I was able to test this product.'),
(4836, 12, 1, 2, '2015-07-13', 'Two Stars Does not toast evenly.'),
(4837, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-21', 'Love, love, love Love the machine. Was not a coffe lover before but love, love the new coffeemaker for the ease of using, the great choices of coffee and the convenience of making one cup.  Thanks Keurig.  Compensated for writing the review'),
