(4846, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'BEST TOASTER! This is the best toaster around.  Woud buy it again knowing what I now know!'),
(4847, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-29', 'Good quality I found this b/c I wanted to update my previous Cuisinart toaster oven - that one is great quality and still works but it\'s scratched up and less pretty, so I wanted a new version of the same model.  However, now it\'s this model: It adds the secure slide-out tray stop which is quite handy, but the control knobs are somewhat hard to read unless you have it in direct strong lighting.'),
(4848, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-21', 'but works great! This is really big (check the size in you have limited counter space), but works great!'),
(4849, 11, 1, 1, '2014-07-13', 'despite knowing that it wouldn\'t come close to how GREAT the old version was (thanks to Amazon reviewers and ... I\'ve had experience with Black & Decker 4 Slice Toasters for decades.  My mom owned and used hers for almost 30+ years.  I owned my Black & Decker 4 Slice Toaster for almost 20 years.  It would still be going strong if I hadn\'t piled all my groceries near the toaster and accidentally placed one bag atop the \"on\" lever.  The toaster burned out from that mishap and I\'ve been heart-broken ever since.  After weeks of review on Amazon and other sites, I decided to buy the newest version of the Black & Decker toaster, despite knowing that it wouldn\'t come close to how GREAT the old version was (thanks to Amazon reviewers and their stories).  Well, I\'ve owned it less than one year and this awful toaster has already broken.  The heating element on the bottom has burned out and the top element doesn\'t heat hot enough to toast a piece of bread...even after turning it on multiple times.  I used this unit less than 5 times per week...hardly a workout for any normal toaster. Before the elements stopped working properly, there were already plenty of reasons why this toaster didn\'t live up to my expectations.  Here are my top three. 1)  You must pick the level of toasting EVERY SINGLE TIME you toast something.  No more finding the \"sweet\" spot and getting perfect toast every time. 2)  The toaster never toasted my bread.  It just DRIED EVERY SPEC of MOISTURE out of the bread and browned the top and bottom.  If you like your toast to have the texture of a crunchy crouton in your mouth, this is the toaster for you. 3)  The unit is HUGE (takes up too much space on my counter) yet the inside of the unit doesn\'t fit 4 slices of normal-sized bread on the provided bread tray.  My old Black & Decker could.  Why call it a 4-slice toaster when you can only squeeze (and I mean squeeze) three slices onto the tray? These are the three main reasons why this unit does not meet my expectations.  I am disappointed, to say the least.  There is no reason why the manufacture couldn\'t produce these units with the same high quality of years past...except to make a buck.  We consumers get the short end of the deal.  What a major bummer!'),
(4850, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-19', 'Watch your food. Otherwise great value Your toast cooks quick! Otherwise, great size and value.'),
(4851, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-16', 'the perfect bremaster For $40 this thing is a steal. Well constructed with just the tight features. Love the variable \"keep warm\" controls, removable water container - which is easy to clean and fill. The hinged coffee access drawer is a snap to use. Unlike other coffee makers, the auto timer has been easy to configure and works flawlessly.'),
(4852, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-02', 'Four Stars Fine, except it could use a timer.'),
(4853, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-11', 'Nice and cheap, I call it a bargain! love the coffee maker, cheap and does the job. Uses cheap non-come filters. Coffee seems good to me. Detachable water tank is a great idea --- but, you will have to be 100% sure the carafe is empty or else you can add a full pot of coffee to a half pot of coffee and produce a flood!'),
(4854, 7, 3, 2, '2015-01-15', 'I purchased this for my elderly father. The ease of convince is great and no problems with the unit, however I will not drink any beverages made with it due to the strong odor of plastic off gas that it emits. I have been making hot chocolate for him every morning 2 weeks and the odor hasn\'t dissipated. I would recommend it to anyone who doesn\'t care about such things.'),
(4855, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'Five Stars Great!'),
(4856, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-03', 'Perfect It works perfect, just what I need!!'),
(4857, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-26', 'Five Stars Works really good'),
(4858, 3, 1, 4, '2014-09-25', 'A good oven for many daily chores, but some things are a bit off mark. The unit has dedicated buttons which autoselect a temperature and cooking time.  I know there is a way to change the preset, but as I lost the instruction manual (again) I have just stumbled over it once or twice when I set up the common tasks.  (frozen pizza temp & time for the brand we favor)  Frozen Snacks, Cake, Cookies, Bread, & Bagel keys.  there is also a convection setting for baking (I use it to make chicken) and it does help with crisping the skin.  The timer is set when selecting the temperature, the problem is that as soon as the temp is reached the timer immediately starts it\'s countdown.  (not a big deal as you and change the temp or time without turning the unit off and on again.  you can also turn convection on or off mid cycle) Now for the things that could be better: This oven is large enough to hold a 12 ct muffin pan or a rectangular cake pan (note without protruding edges on the end.  The description says it will cook a 12\" pizza and while that is true you need to have a pizza pan to support the edges of the crust, it can not be placed directly on the wire rack as the edges will droop off the wire rack.  Muffins come out fine, but more delicate cakes do not seem to properly rise.  Examining further this is due to a gap between the glass door and the frame of the oven, the resulting cool spot impacts rising of more touchy baked items.  Muffins are fine as well as a bundt pan, but a rectangular pan will rise unevenly.  Cupcakes need to be rotated twice during baking so they all rise equally.  the alternative which i finally did was to use a piece of silicone cutting board that had been damaged to fill the space between the door and frame.  Since  this was also baking temp rated to 500 I don\'t have worries about it burning or melting and the baked items do have a more consistent rise.  (although I still turn them)  The oven does go up to 450 for Broil, and I frequently use it to cook fish or steaks.  Just be prepared to wait 15 or so minutes to reach that temp.  Living in Florida I do like this oven because I can take it out on the back patio in the summer to cook and not need to heat the entire condo.  Unit cleans up nicely, although the button descriptions do seem to come off somewhat easily.  We got this 2nd one when we got a new roommate.  She liked the oven but had no idea what keys were for what functions.  After I explained it to her she loved the oven and bought us a new one 2 months later.'),
(4859, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'Five Stars Great programable pot of coffee, very hot! Takes about 10 min to brew, awesome!'),
(4860, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-17', 'Simple functional toaster that toasts bread evenly. Simple functional toaster that toasts bread evenly. Doesn\'t get hot on the outside. So far I have only used it for bread.'),
(4861, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-10', 'Terribly unhappy. Bought this wanting to make smoothies and it does NOT work. The blades won\'t turn and even when they do, they don\'t have enough power to blend fruit (which isn\'t frozen, it\'s fresh). Would not buy again. Wanted to return, but now I can\'t even do that. Terribly unhappy.'),
