(4877, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-30', 'Five Stars works as advertised'),
(4878, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Very versatile and easy to operate Very versatile and easy to operate.  The defrost \"cycle\" is especially handy for me.  Holds a variety of breads and sizes.'),
(4879, 8, 1, 3, '2015-06-27', 'Not bad it\'s doing the job for us coffee drinkers Not bad it\'s doing the job for us coffee drinkers,but when I placed the order for a black & decker I got a black + decker it\'s like an off brand to the black & decker I previously had until I broke upon moving. But none the less it\'s still a good product'),
(4880, 5, 1, 5, '2016-12-01', 'Five Stars good coffee.'),
(4881, 5, 1, 4, '2015-06-06', 'Good but could be better Slow drip. Also, not very warm. My cheaper coffee pot preformed better _'),
(4882, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-07', 'Perfect No-Frills Toaster I\'ll echo other reviews. This is a no-frills toaster with all of the options you will ever need. Toaster includes the Bagel option that I love, and oversized slices fit it perfectly!'),
(4883, 3, 1, 3, '2016-06-02', 'Three Stars Cooks good but door flops open without any kind of stops.'),
(4884, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-25', 'Great coffee maker, but restrictions on pods shouldn\'t be there This is our first Keurig brewer and so far I really like it. Brewing is very quick and convenient. After powering it on, it usually takes 1-2 minutes to preheat the water, and then brewing a cup of coffee takes less than a minute. For a standard K-cup, there are options to brew several different size cups, and there\'s also a \"strong\" option that injects water into the cup a little slower so you end up with stronger coffee. It\'s ready to brew another cup almost immediately after that. Generally I can get 4 or 5 8oz cups before having to refill the water reservoir. I like that it has a built in/replaceable filter, so I don\'t need to worry about filtering the water before filling it up. The digital touch screen is also backlit, which allows for easy brewing in the mornings when it\'s a bit too early to turn on the lights. Super easy cleanup compared to a traditional coffee maker is also a plus. I also purchased the Keurig carafe (not included with this model) and tried a few of the carafe pods. Everything worked as expected - having the option to brew several cups at once is nice. I did find that the coffee brewed this way was somewhat weaker, but that could have been due to the specific pod I was using. The reason I\'m giving only four stars is because of the way these 2.0 machines are designed to only work with Keurig-branded pods. So far, this hasn\'t affected me specifically (all of the pods I\'ve tried have worked), and defeating this \"feature\" is supposed to be trivial, but I hate the idea of DRM on anything, let alone on my coffee. Also, Keurig is offering free boxes of K-cups in exchange for \"honest\" reviews. I\'m obviously taking advantage of that myself, but be aware that this may influence the reviews here. At any rate - Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4885, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-09', 'This is the best coffee maker I\'ve ever owned This is the best coffee maker I\'ve ever owned, hands down. I love that the water canister on the back is removable and washable. I love everything about this coffee maker.'),
(4886, 3, 1, 4, '2016-03-08', 'Four Stars Like it, but the button names are very faint, need good light to see what your pushing?'),
(4887, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-22', 'Great toaster value Very feature rich toaster.  Makes perfect toast and looks good.'),
(4888, 3, 1, 4, '2015-02-04', 'Love having an extra oven when cooking for holidays Bought this mainly for toast, but find myself using the convection oven for many things - roasting veggies, baking potato spears, heating pizza, toasting nuts.  Love having an extra oven  when cooking for holidays.  Heats quickly and evenly, and is done cooking in about 2/3rds the time of conventional oven.  Only negative, as others have mentioned, is it gets burning hot all over the outside.  With my previous toaster oven we were able to leave stuff on top of it, and did not have to pull it out from under cabinets before using.  Have not yet used it in the summer, and am wondering if it will heat up the kitchen.  But as long as you are aware of this, and  keep kids away from it,  this is a great toaster oven for a very reasonable price.'),
(4889, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-23', 'Four Stars I was disappointed that it doesn\'t have a timer!'),
(4890, 6, 1, 2, '2016-11-06', 'which I loved. This toaster I bought this toaster to replace an older Cusinart toaster, which I loved.  This toaster, not so much, though.  My old Cuisinart had 10 darkness settings,which I set at between 8 or 9 to toast whole grain breads that take longer to toast.  This toaster only has 7 levels, and number 7 only toasts to pale blonde, so I have to toast twice to get to the right darkness.'),
(4891, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-22', 'Five Stars Thank you!'),
(4892, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-18', 'Great product Replaced this with my Keurig. So much better and extremely pleased with this product. Very simple and common sense product. Love it!  Bigger than I thought it was going to be, though.'),
(4893, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-10', 'Toaster This is wonderful.'),
(4894, 8, 1, 5, '2014-11-03', 'Five Stars Perfect for one. Easy to use and clean.'),
(4895, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-25', 'Five Stars We like the coffee it make very well'),
(4896, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-23', 'A nice no frills toaster with enough features!  Solid performer! Nice no frills toaster!  We needed another toaster for gluten free items and this one fits the bill.  Inexpensive and does the job with enough features.  Nice job Cuisinart!'),
(4897, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-17', 'Five Stars super price and it couldn\'t be a better product!'),
(4898, 5, 1, 3, '2014-05-13', 'Buyer Beware I purchased this coffee maker on March 3rd. On May 10th the Auto Set stopped working; The very trait I was looking for in an automatic coffee maker. Too bad.'),
(4899, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-20', 'Five Stars Great appliance - haven\'t burnt anything yet!!  Toaster mode works very well! So far so good!'),
(4900, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-26', 'Five Stars Glad I order it  perfect white'),
(4901, 11, 1, 5, '2014-01-15', 'Nice toaster oven Looks great and heats up fast. Cooks evenly and it is easy to clean up the crumbs by removing the crumb tray.'),
(4902, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-02', 'Five Stars Easy to use, easy to clean'),
(4903, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-24', 'love these blenders love these blenders, they are the best its like the 4th one I purchased. have one at work, home and vacation house'),
(4904, 4, 1, 4, '2015-10-06', 'This does the best job of toasting bread I have had a variety of toaster ovens. This does the best job of toasting bread. All its features are quite good. I just wish it had a temperature gauge to let you know when oven is preheated.'),
(4905, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Major benefits and only 1 minor flaw I love this toaster oven for most of my cooking needs.  It heats quickly and does a great job with all my food.  It has the flexibility I expect with a toaster oven and then some.  The clean-up is easy thanks to the slide out drawer.  I only look at toaster ovens where the drawer pulls out when you open the drawer.  This does not pull out quite as far as my last but it gets the job done. The only fault I have found, and it is minor, is that the bars on the rack are spaced quite a bit further apart than what this replaced.  Under most circumstances this probably is not a problem.  I like to make frozen hashbrown patties in it and with this model when I flip them at the half way point, they are just wide enough apart that the sides/corners of the patty like to droop down between them.  I have started putting the roasting rack upside down to double the amount of bars which seems to help.  Since this is a very specific use I did not dock any stars but is something you might want to be aware of. I still recommend this as a high quality, high value toaster oven.'),
(4906, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-29', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(4907, 8, 1, 1, '2016-07-12', 'The first and the last time i will buy from ... The first and the last time i will buy from Black+ Decker, bought it form my office and fill it up to turn on in the morning when i get to work, just to find out all the water had spilled out all gotten all over my paperwork and keyboard.'),
(4908, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-09', 'Four Stars A little hard to use, my grandma has trouble toasting every time. Sometimes it doesn\'t toast properly/bake/broil properly'),
(4909, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-17', 'This is a great oven, but does not \"shut off\" as did ... This is a great oven, but does not \"shut off\" as did every toaster oven I\'ve owned over the years.'),
(4910, 12, 1, 2, '2016-11-30', 'Two Stars Too small wrongly described.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(4911, 7, 3, 5, '2016-06-04', 'I\'ve been through three Keurigs, one Mr. Coffee k-brewer and a scoop brewer by Hamilton Beach. This one by far makes better coffee, and I like that I can choose regular or bold. You can use ground coffee or k-cups or pods.... nice to have a choice! For the price and function of this machine, I\'ll never waste money on another expensive Keurig, that I know will break within a year!'),
(4912, 7, 3, 1, '2016-10-14', 'Worst coffee pot ever purchased. Bought at WalMart. Put 8oz in and 2 oz comes out. Restart to get another 2 oz. Do it a third time and get another 1-2 oz. Rest of water will just drip out over time onto counter. Only used it approx. 10 times. Can\'t take it back receipt thrown away. No use donating it if it\'s no good!'),
(4913, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', '2.0 worth it to upgrade I am glad I finally upgraded to the 2.0. My old Keurig works fine but the new one takes up way less space on my counter. There 2.0 delivers a fast and hot cup of coffee each time. I like the new features like reminders to change the filter or descaling. Thanks,Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4914, 5, 1, 2, '2015-07-24', 'Base Plate Disintegrates After only two months of use, the base plate started to disintegrate. Now at five months, the base plate is actually starting to break off. Not a quality product.'),
(4915, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-23', 'One Star Useless, please do not buy it, you will regret it. The motor burned out within 2 days.'),
(4916, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Five Stars Works great and doesn\'t take up much space like other toaster ovens!.'),
(4917, 5, 1, 4, '2014-11-29', 'Can\'t Complain This product is solid. I do love the easy water container and it has little wheels on it so I can slide it out from against my backsplash and simply add water. I am not a coffee connoisseur but it makes a solid cup of coffee for me. Its simple enough to set up the timer and clock that even my mom can do it. And she is horrible with electronics and she knows it lol. I have not had any problems with it dripping or spilling. The one CON I have is that it seems a little cheap. The handle of the carafe creaks a little and the plastic of the back seems pretty cheap. My old $10 4 cup Mr. Coffee feels more sturdy. But I don\'t think Hamilton Beach is known for the best quality materials. Its not a problem for me, but if you\'re looking for a high end machine that feels expensive then you should pass on this maker. I have been using this daily for a few months and its still working great.'),
(4918, 4, 1, 4, '2016-06-20', 'Pretty Good Toaster Oven, But Better Options Out There We\'ve been using this toaster oven for about 5 years and it\'s worked for us.  We only use the toast and bake functions.  Our main use is to heat/toast bread and leftover food (sandwiches, pizza, chicken, steak, etc.).  You do have to play around with it and get used to how it works.  We\'ll put in on medium when toasting bread, but when the timer goes off the bread it almost burnt.  So we\'ll take it out before the timer or put it on a lesser setting.  Honestly, it\'s not the best toaster oven and we\'d gladly spend more money to get something better, but it\'s been working for us after we got used to it.  At this point we\'re just using it until it stops working or we just get tired of it.'),
(4919, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-11', 'I am BEYOND impressed by this coffee maker by Hamiliton Beach, I have always been a huge fan of their products I have to ay they have really out done themselves with this on-of-a-kind coffee maker,why,do yu ask<>? First,let me tell you for oe I really wanted the Keruig after trying this incredible and very affordable cooffemaker I a sold on it and its many features that other makers just do not have ,I was literally blown away with what this beautifyl machine can do,by just a pres of a button,it is also very helpful to fill a up or a mug simply by moving yhe plate that is under the the spout, I told you about that first, it has a removable single serv pack holder I lve it,you save soo much money you want just one cup of coffe yu just fill this little guy up and place it in,there you go,how easy is that?It also has a brew basket if you want to make more than one cup this maker is incredible, I love it and it als does the K cups just make sure you do not remove the foil:) I am thrilled with my Namiliton Beach flex brew single-serve coffeemaker and so will you,it has replaced my cofee maker and this is going to be such a money -saving tool and the best part,it taste out of his world:) I have received this prodct free for my honest feedback for beig a part of the Wal mart spark reviewer team:)'),
(4920, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-17', 'Five Stars best coffee maker ever'),
(4921, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-30', 'Replacement for Keurig After one broken Keurig and a hard look at what kcups were really costing us, we decided to go back to basics. This coffee maker rocks - and the coffee tastes much better than that which was brewed through our Keurig. I\'ll still use the Keurig for parties, but for daily use, this machine is the best.'),
(4922, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-02', 'Five Stars my favorite blender'),
(4923, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-21', 'but you can see if it\'s almost done the way you like it and then turn it off we use it almost everyday.  the timer for the toast is somewhat tricky to get it just right, but you can see if it\'s almost done the way you like it and then turn it off.  it\'s nice and small-ish so it takes little room in our small kitchen. we haven\'t tried with other foods like pizza or steak... i had a B+D toaster oven before so i\'m pretty sure it\'ll work for anything.'),
(4924, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-24', 'Can\'t go wrong. Purchased for me out of my wishlist to replace an old... OLD coffee maker. Honestly, it\'s wonderful. Hot coffee, timer; so far, it\'s been amazing.'),
(4925, 7, 3, 5, '2016-10-10', 'My last coffee marker jumped ship,LOL. When looking at all that Walmart had to offer,I chose this. Hamilton Beach Single Serve Plus! It has it\'s own baskets to make different size coffee\'s. You can use the k-cups or your own refillable k-cups. The switch to brew are dual purpose. Upper switch for regular brew or the bottom for bold and that one is my Fav!'),
(4926, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Coffee maker So far good'),
(4927, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-05', 'I love this toaster! I like everything about this toaster. Toasts fast and even. Easy to wipe off. Love the \"lift\" feature to raise smaller bread slices up so no burnt fingers.'),
(4928, 4, 1, 1, '2015-10-31', 'Do Not Buy! Stay far away from this one.  Purchased one through Amazon 5/2013.  It lasted about 2 years until the bottom element burnt out.  Found out that it could not be repaired.  Made the mistake of buying a second one (4/2015) as a replacement.  This one lasted about 6 months before it decided not to turn off.  The only way to shut it down is unplug it.  Tried several times to contact Cuisinart customer service for Warranty, Gave up after 20 minutes each time.  I will continue to try and contact them.  Do yourself  a favor and buy something else.'),
(4929, 9, 1, 3, '2015-02-06', 'The unit makes reasonable coffee, but the \"Coffee Gauge\" ... The unit makes reasonable coffee, but the \"Coffee Gauge\" didn\'t work from the moment we opened it. Does anyone know of a fix for this?'),
(4930, 6, 1, 4, '2015-12-30', 'four star Good looking product at good price'),
(4931, 9, 1, 2, '2016-04-23', 'Why is this happening??? I like the look of the unit and the coffee tastes good BUT once I fill one cup of coffee the pot continues dripping coffee until all the coffee in the dispenser is gone. As you can imagine if you didn\'t have a cup ready underneath, this would make a terrible mess. Why is this happening?'),
(4932, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-24', 'Does what it has to do, i only give ... Does what it has to do, i only give this product 4 stars because I was under the impression of having a wider toster oven.'),
(4933, 11, 1, 1, '2015-07-19', 'Black and Decker nameplate now indicates flimsy, poorly designed junk Whatever Asian entity now owns the Black and Decker nameplate is producing flimsy, poorly designed junk. I usually use a toaster oven to make toast or cheese toast, at most 2 slices at a time. I got the TO1332SBD  to replace my Black and Decker TRO60 toaster oven circa 1988. After more than 20 years, it was losing its ability to toast. I didn\'t want the B&D toaster oven with the 3 knobs because who wants to set 3 knobs to make toast? The old B&D toaster oven had one simple lever to initiate toasting. (The ability to toast different degrees of toastiness broke soon after I got it, but that was okay -- one kind of toast was enough for me.) So I got this 2-knob toaster oven on sale. Overall, the industrial design rates a flabby C minus. The device seems flimsy and toy-like. Esthetically, it is ungalnly. The interior capacity is smaller than my old toaster oven, but the exterior dimensions are larger. It has an outsized plastic handle. Setting 2 knobs to toast is still unaccountably complicated. The power cord is ridiculously short. I suspect the device will last months rather than decades. One thing everyone should understand about this toaster oven: It does not have the kind of crumb tray that folds out from the bottom. It does not actually have a crumb tray at all. The bottom is sealed and a flat metal liner (easily mistaken for a cookie sheet) is provided to catch the crumbs. Anyone who has dealt with crumbs will see instantly that you will not be able to remove this liner with the crumbs on it. It is worthless. Have your vacuum ready to suck up the crumbs. (I line the bottom of my toaster oven with aluminum foil to keep it clean.) Inaugural toast samples were poor: One side slightly burned while the other lightly toasted. The toasting quality matches that of my dying B&D toaster oven, no improvement there. You need to watch it while it\'s working. There is no thermostat or smoke detector to shut the toaster oven off if something starts to burn. If you\'ve set the temperature too high or for too long, you could start a fire. The old toaster oven was a cheap piece of junk then, but compared to the new toaster oven, it was sturdy, well-designed, and reliable. I will definitely think twice before buying a Black and Decker appliance again.'),
(4934, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-03', 'GREAT! Spoiling my wife and I every morning... Researched coffee makers and settled on this little jewel. Love this coffee maker! We\'ve enjoyed using it every morning since we purchased it in 2013. The design is very intuitive, convenient and seems to be a product that will last. Certainly we will sad if this ever stops working. The only way this would be better is if it came with a robot to grind my coffee and have it ready when I roll out of bed. But, let\'s be honest... I kind of like doing that myself. Great purchase. Highly recommended for yourself or as gift to newly weds, someone whom likes coffee, housewarming or whatever. I\'d be surprised if someone didn\'t like this one.'),
(4935, 5, 1, 5, '2014-05-22', 'Excellent coffee maker - beats the competition We bought this coffee maker 1 month ago based upon the thoughtful positive reviews of TVR and Alan H.  Their comments are accurate and we are very pleased with the performance of this product.  We have owned many competitor products (most recently, 3  Cuisinart DCC 1200 Brew Central units) and found them inferior to this Hamilton Beach coffee maker because of difficulty in filling the water reservoir and spilling from the pour spout of the pot.  They both brew good coffee in the same amount of time - we always use the Bold setting on the HB, just as we always used the 1-4 cup option on the Cuisinart, because we use a Krups coffee grinder that always produces a finely ground product.  (Btw, the Krups grinder is not recommended because you never can get other than finely ground coffee). The one negative to the HB 46201 is that it lacks an automatic shut off.  No modern electric appliances should be allowed to be sold without this as a standard safety feature.  Who wants coffee that has been sitting for more than an hour on a hot burner anyhow? Our other pet peeve, is that all coffee makers should have an easily replaceable heater/siphon.  Without that, no matter how you clean and maintain your unit, it will have a limited lifetime (1-2 years, assuming 1-2 pots per day), even with filtered water use.'),
(4936, 4, 1, 4, '2015-07-16', 'I don\'t like it as much as the old one (10 year ... We bought this at Bed Bath and Beyond about a month ago when our old toaster broke.  I don\'t like it as much as the old one (10 year old Black and Decker).  It seems to get hotter on the outside and the beep sounds a bit like a smoke detector.  It also seems more likely to burn things but that might just be an adjustment I need to make (I think I almost have it figured out, I make toaster waffles with it most often and if I toast them twice on low that seems to work well).'),
(4937, 4, 1, 4, '2016-03-01', 'Lasted 4 years before 1 burner \"died\" The lower burner stopped working at just less than 4 years, so I am back to buy another toaster oven, and wondering if a different brand would last more than 4 years. The Cuisinart TOB-40 is simple to operate.  In TOAST or BAGEL modes, the oven shuts itself off automatically.  On BAKE you need to manually turn off the oven, as it stays \"on\".  We cook hot dogs, reheat food that would get soggy in a microwave, and make toast.  I like that it is easy to change the height of the shelf by just turning the shelf upside down.'),
(4938, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-21', 'Blends like a charm The size is deceiving. Blends like a charm. I highly recommend it.'),
(4939, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-06', 'We just love this coffeemaker We just love this coffeemaker.  Was looking for one without the carafe, just a long as it is still easy to clean, and this definitely fit the bill.  Love how you dont have to wait for the entire batch to brew to start drinking some.  Easy to add the water, easy to clean out the used grounds, and makes a great cup of coffee that stays fresh for longer than the standard carafe design, in my opinion (and I owned a coffee shop for over a decade, so I would know).  Overall Im very pleased and would highly recommend.  Honestly dont see any downsides with this design.'),
(4940, 5, 1, 4, '2014-09-12', 'Nice coffee maker for the price Nice coffee maker for the price, makes a fine cup of coffee.  The only 2 negatives are;  1. When the coffee is made this is no notification that the coffee is done.  2. I provide addition heat to make the coffee hot enough.  I put in in the microwave for an addition 30 seconds to hit the coffee to what I deem as proper temperature.'),
(4941, 3, 1, 3, '2016-04-30', 'Sad day Bought this toaster Aug 2013, used almost daily. Died today. Thought it might last longer- not sure if will purchase again.'),
(4942, 2, 1, 4, '2016-06-14', 'Four Stars I got it for my husband....he uses it all the time and he likes it'),
(4943, 5, 1, 4, '2016-10-11', 'Four Stars Great coffee maker. Easy to clean, I really like the removable water tank.'),
(4944, 10, 1, 4, '2016-04-20', 'Convenient! Small, portable, and good for a quick smoothie. Best thing is, the blender itself is a cup! Great idea.'),
(4945, 1, 1, 4, '2016-05-04', 'A very good machine I wish it had a timer for morning wake up coffee'),
(4946, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-14', 'Five Stars Great appliance, thank you!!'),
(4947, 3, 1, 4, '2016-02-04', 'Love it, except to program it Love it, except to program it, when you push the buttons it is LOUD! Annoys the heck out of me, but maybe that is being too picky. It does work good.'),
(4948, 7, 3, 1, '2014-02-28', 'In fact my friend is looking for a single serve pot and I told her not to buy this product. I wanted this for my desk at work. Every time I want a cup of coffee, I have to go get water, there is no storage water tank on it. I have tried the K-cups and coffee, but both spray/leak water/coffee all over. My cup was only _ full with the rest on my desk. I have tried it several times making sure everything everything is perfectly, but still caused a mess. This was a gift from my husband and hated to tell him I was happy with it; but what a waste of money. It may be cheaper, but still NOT WORTH IT.'),
(4949, 7, 3, 1, '2016-01-12', 'This item will NOT brew various sizes. It only brews a maximum of 10 oz of water. There\'s no filling a travel mug. Second, when you try to brew a prepak it promptly plugs up the water dispenser that forces water into the pak and out the bottom resulting in the water in the tank steaming and boiling away and no coffee being made. In other words the thing just plain doesn\'t work. I returned this item as defective. I do want to thank Walmart for their liberal return policy and the ease of returning on online purchase at my local store.'),
(4950, 9, 1, 1, '2015-02-17', 'not a good product for the one cup/day type like me Where to start.  First of all, the coffee does not come out hot!  I put my cup in the microwave after it comes out.  Second,cleanup is not any easier than in the traditional coffee maker.  In fact, it\'s a little harder with the need to rinse multiple pieces.  Third, it takes a long time to make a cup of coffee.  The brewing takes longer than usual, dispensing the coffee is painfully slow, and then I need to microwave for 30 seconds. Maybe, if I needed a large capacity coffee maker, I would appreciate this a little more.  As it stands, not a good product for the one cup/day type like me.'),
(4951, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-29', 'The \'Cadillac\' of coffee makers! A super coffee maker!  I\'m so glad the well can be removed for cleaning, and it\'s much more \'user friendly\' than the Black & Decker model we had.  Would highly recommend!'),
(4952, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-22', 'Love this coffee pot Love this coffee pot.  Purchased the permanent filter that goes with it and couldn\'t be more pleased.  I am a simple drip coffee girl, so I don\'t need a ton of bells and whistles.  I used the program feature a few times and it works just fine, but I prefer to just set up the pot in the morning.  My favorite part of this coffee maker is the water tank/reserve.  The whole thing comes up and off and the top flips off.  Makes filling up the water reserve very easy.'),
(4953, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-15', 'This toaster oven is PERFECT for baking things so I can stay healthy while ... I frequently go on extended travel to the same hotel in Maryland (they will store items for me while I am gone). They have a cooktop in the room but no oven. This toaster oven is PERFECT for baking things so I can stay healthy while I am away! You cannot beat the quality for the price.'),
(4954, 11, 1, 5, '2016-01-01', 'Great! Bought it for my dad. Great!'),
(4955, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'Five Stars Bought for my wife she loves it'),
(4956, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-21', 'Great little blender. Already have one, but wanted another for work. Great for smoothies. Not for large ice cubes; works best with crushed ice or frozen fruit.'),
(4957, 5, 1, 1, '2015-10-06', 'Worked for a couple months...... Worked great for almost 2 months and has now died. Woke up this morning to coffee not made and now power to the unit at all. I tried other plugins and still hadn\'t turned back on. There appears to be no reset button. If this is going to happen for a nice coffee maker might as well go cheap so I\'m not spending so much the next time it happens.'),
(4958, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-31', 'This thing is great. I use it almost daily This thing is great. I use it almost daily. Pros: Plenty of settings, cooks evenly, decent size (about the size of a small-medium sized microwave) and excellent price. Cons: Sometimes it feels like it take a little long to get up to preheat temperatures, and the labels on the buttons are pretty hard to see. Would be nice if they lit up, but that would probably add too much to manufacturing cost at this price point.'),
(4959, 7, 3, 2, '2014-03-13', 'I liked the coffee maker at first. It was a little slow but not too bad. After 5 months, won\'t make a cup all at once. It shuts off in the middle of making the cup for no reason. Turn it back on and sometimes it finishes making that cup or might make part of the rest but then shuts off again!!!'),
(4960, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-18', 'Great Product! Effective, Efficient and Stylish I really like this brewer. I upgrade from a Keurig Mini Brewer to this Keurig 2.0 K250. The touch screen is very user friendly. You can brew 4, 6, 8, or 10 oz, plus the carafe! It also has the \"strong\" option which is very useful when I have guess over that like very strong coffee. Additionally, the design is very stylish and accommodates for more water storage, so you don\'t have to fill it over and over. It is noisier than my previous Keurig model, but it is not bad and it is definitely worth it for the improved features and design.  This machine allows everyone to pick their individual drink and enjoy. The brewing system really brings out the flavor of any coffee. For my kids, I use it for teas and hot cocoa. It\'s easy to use and your drinks are ready quickly. It\'s an awesome choice! Definitely try one out, as it is well worth the money. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(4961, 4, 1, 4, '2015-09-26', 'Four Stars A little difficult to see the options and some difficulty getting toast just right'),
(4962, 12, 1, 2, '2016-08-14', 'Not Big Enough for a Toaster Oven Oven is too small, there is no button to pop up the toast early and it\'s flimsy.  Just got it and wish I had seen it in real life instead of ordering online.  It functions to toast, but in our opinion we bought the wrong toaster oven.  Our plan was to be able to use the oven part for cooking tasks as we are high energy cooks, but this is a joke.'),
(4963, 6, 1, 5, '2016-05-14', 'I use #3 setting for a nice dark toast Works well, and toasts in the usual time for toasters.  I use #3 setting for a nice dark toast.'),
(4964, 9, 1, 1, '2015-11-27', 'Like the idea of how the coffee is disbursed Like the idea of how the coffee is disbursed, but the coffee is not hot, so if you like it hot I would decline on this purchase. I would send back if I had to save the box.'),
(4965, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-12', 'stylish and large Finally replaced my Oster Toaster Oven with this one and oh so happy.  Heats up quickly, maintains the proper temp. [major reason why i had to toss old one], and love the fact it can handle two (2) personal sized pizzas at once.  and for the $$$??? can\'t be beat.  Local retailer had advertised for $32. more'),
(4966, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-20', 'Absolutely awesome! I\'ve been using this brew system for about a month now and I love it! It\'s very fast and the brew sizes are perfect! I think one of my favorite features is that it is touch screen! There are so many kcup choices I\'ve bascially stopped buying coffee from coffee based chains and just exclusively used my Keurig! I received my Keurig from Influester as a promotional item to test and review :) it has been a success!'),
(4967, 9, 1, 1, '2015-07-02', 'One Star not so, it will take 20 minutes to warm your coffee'),
(4968, 3, 1, 5, '2015-10-06', 'Hopefully it lasts as long 10 years with twice a day use and works as good as my last one Just ordered it.  Hopefully it lasts as long 10 years with twice a day use and works as good as my last one.  This one measures a bit bigger and a lists to be a bit lighter than my old old,  May it RIP.'),
(4969, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Great for busy parents! I\'ve been wanting a Keurig for years now & finally got one! I\'m in love! It\'s so easy to use! As a working Mom of a busy 2 year old girl I don\'t have much time to make coffee so this has been great! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(4970, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-02', 'Five Stars Works as advertised. My first one, so we will see about durability.'),
(4971, 4, 1, 3, '2015-02-08', 'Three Stars I returned it because none of those three knobs is a timer.'),
(4972, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-24', 'Five Stars it toasts my bread perfectly!!!'),
(4973, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Five Stars Easy to use, easy to clean.'),
(4974, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-05', 'Five Stars This is one of the best coffee pots I\'ve ever owned. Brews coffee fast, hot, and delicious. Setting it up takes a bit getting used to because of the different reservoirs you need to take care of, but that\'s quickly overcome.'),
(4975, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-01', 'Great coffee maker. This item is great. I\'m happy I bough it. Durable and easy to recommend to many. Will buy again. Niceeeeee.'),
(4976, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-10', 'Upgraded from the classic... Love this new Keurig brewing system! The touchscreen is one of my favorite parts! & the option for larger cups & to brew strong! I had a special edition older Keurig before this upgrade! It will be hard to let go of my classic Keurig but this one will def see a lot of use! So glad I got this one FREE for testing purposes!'),
(4977, 4, 1, 2, '2015-04-18', 'Short Life Span It was good at first...until the heating unit on the bottom split open after only 2 years of use.  Cusinart will replace the unit but I am responsible to pay return shipping and shipping of the new unit.  I can\'t believe this broke after 2 years!  My previous toaster from DeLonghi lasted 10 years.'),
(4978, 9, 1, 5, '2016-06-27', 'Awesome coffee maker! I conducted a lot of research before purchasing my first coffee maker and this one works great! I should have read the instructions before I made my very first cup but my mom and friends approve!'),
(4979, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-02', 'Very disappointed I received the Hamilton beach 51101b with no lid so I could never use it. I do not live In USA so I could not return the product.'),
(4980, 5, 1, 3, '2015-10-06', 'Great while it lasted I bought this product in November of 2014, It is now October of 2015 and it quit working.  Great while it lasted, but not very long in my opinion.  Not even a year?'),
(4981, 8, 1, 3, '2016-10-25', 'but it is fine. I didn\'t read close enough so didn\'t realize this was only a 5 cup coffee maker, but it is fine.'),
(4982, 2, 1, 3, '2015-07-20', 'Three Stars Decent toaster, but it is really small.'),
(4983, 12, 1, 1, '2016-09-06', 'Horrible quality! REALLLLLLY small. Toaster part didn\'t stay down...had to hold it yourself to get anything toasted.... nobody has time for THAT! So.....NOT keeping!.'),
(4984, 12, 1, 4, '2014-08-09', 'Four Stars fantastic, we have a camper the size is just what I needed, and it works great.'),
(4985, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-02', 'Works fine. As advertised.  Works fine.'),
(4986, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-01', 'Five Stars Works like a charm!'),
(4987, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-29', 'Needs econo filter with packaging. Just had my first cup this morning.  Great so far.  Warmer keeps coffee hot for many cups.  Would like for the filter to be available on Amazon at a reasonable price.  $9.99 seems a bit steep and a gotcha from the company since I\'m not a fan of buying bottled water and my water is not very good.'),
(4988, 2, 1, 2, '2015-04-22', 'I feel like I got burnt buying this toaster. This makes a decent piece of toast if you get the setting EXACTLY right which seems very difficult to pinpoint accurately. I don\'t have the hang of it so I have to keep an eye on it or the toast will get burnt. The ceiling is so close to the rack that if you put a roll in you  have to make sure it is really flat at the hinge or the edges will get burnt since they are too close to the top element. I haven\'t even bothered to try using it as an oven since the headroom is so small. I don\'t understand how it is a \"top seller\" on Amazon. I guess it is cheap.  I want to return it but it will cost half the price of the toaster just to ship it back. I already had to rearrange half my countertop because the cord is so short. This toaster is more trouble than it is worth. I should have paid more attention to the negative reviews.'),
(4989, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-01', 'Five Stars Good.'),
(4990, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Heats up fast.  Easy and convenient to use. Heats up fast.  Easy and convenient to use. Nice big cooking area.'),
(4991, 4, 1, 5, '2015-09-10', 'Five Stars I am very satisfied with this Toaster Oven.  It is Large and easy to use.'),
(4992, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-20', 'Great product, fast shipping Great product, fast shipping, wish I had known it only takes certain K Cups though. Easy to hack that though although a bit annoying.'),
(4993, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-16', 'Five Stars Excellent toaster oven'),
(4994, 4, 1, 5, '2016-10-16', 'SOLID! So many of the newer toaster ovens have flimsy control knobs and/or controls that are not easy to understand! These controls are simple and well-made; easy to clean with the pullout tray; door closing mechanism is solid.'),
(4995, 4, 1, 4, '2016-01-14', 'Nice toaster oven, but the toast is done sound is WAY TOO LOUD The toaster is great and has easy to use controls to use as a toaster or an oven and looks nice.  My compliant on this item is, when your toast is done the sound is SO LOUD, when I first heard it I thought it was the fire alarm.  We have looked for ways to turn it down and can\'t find anyway.  It\'s is VERY loud.'),
(4996, 5, 1, 1, '2016-05-30', 'Never buying again Got this December 30 and it has already stopped working. The front cover for the buttons constantly popped off every time we put the coffee filter it. Now it will not even turn on.'),
(4997, 3, 1, 5, '2014-11-21', '... a gift but the recipient states that it is wonderful and works great for baking It was purchased as a gift but the recipient states that it is wonderful and works great for baking, etc.'),
(4998, 7, 3, 2, '2016-01-13', 'I bought this after my old one finally bit the dust. One: if you want a fast cup of coffee, this is not for you. Second: If you want a hot cup of coffee, this is not for you. I found that it took quite a long time for it to brew (I use ground coffee). My old one was much faster by a long shot. I like my coffee good and hot because I use a thermal mug and drink it while working on the computer. The older model of \"flexbrew\" machines work so much better than the newer ones.'),
(4999, 5, 1, 3, '2014-01-20', 'disappointed. after reading all the reviews i was so excited to get this coffee maker.  Imagine my surprise when it kept overflowing the grounds into the coffee.  so bummed.  i tried different filters, different amounts of coffee...  it did it every time.  bye-bye hamilton beach coffee maker, i\'m going back to cuisinart.  OH!!!  the timer was great :)'),
(5000, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-29', 'worth the money this is an excellent coffee maker very well made not cheap plastic easy to use and love the light when poring coffee into the cup.'),
(5001, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Great features. I had 14 people (all serious coffee dinkers) staying at my house for a funeral. For three mornings this coffee maker was a workhorse. The best thing about this coffee maker is the removable water resevoir. After a pot was made, I was able to fill the resevoir, have a filter of fresh coffee grounds ready to make the next pot. So much easier than having to fill the pot and then pour it back into the coffeemaker. Aside from that, this coffeemaker does what all the rest do, make good hot coffee. I will buy this coffeemaker again.'),
(5002, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-14', 'Five Stars Love this item!'),
(5003, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-07', 'Five Stars useful'),
(5004, 9, 1, 2, '2015-04-30', 'Not a good purchase I would never purchase this coffee pot again.  The design is flawed and water drips down in to the reservoir when the lid is opened.  That has to be cleaned up before another pot of coffee can be made.  I read all those reviews and thought very good.  Ha!  Will not take reviews as gospel ever again. Do not take this review as gospel either.'),
(5005, 6, 1, 3, '2016-02-10', 'Three Stars Settings don\'t coincide with how it toasts.'),
(5006, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Simply awesome! I\'m on my 2nd Simply awesome!  I\'m on my 2nd.  1st one died after 5+ years.  I\'m a kitchen utensil/product snob and only like the top/most-efficient-for-their-function brands.  No \"luxury\" brands make a toastation. It\'s a space-saver and does the job great.  I use it almost everyday. Only con: a bit hard to clean--> Suggestion: Line the little tray with foil and wrap around the edges.  I throw this one out every couple days.  Keeps everything clean and no crazy cleanup. **For anyone thinking of getting the newer model.  It sucks.  I bought it, saw it didn\'t have a bunch of the features this model has and a couple new annoying ones.  Sent it right back and bought this version. New version of it, which sucks: -NO PULL OUT TRAY.  Why in the world would Hamilton Beach do away with the retractable tray feature??  I don\'t know. -SMALLER TOP SLOT: The top slot opening is NOT as wide (\'thick\") as the older model. So you\'d have to cram your bagel in there. -No crumb tray -New annoying beeping sound that isn\'t efficient.  Who needs more noise in their life? Save your time, get this \"older\" version. You\'ll be glad you did.'),
(5007, 8, 1, 3, '2016-05-05', 'Three Stars This stuff a very simple but\'em a little be an enough something else...somehow...that\'s okay...thanks u'),
(5008, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-03', 'An Excellent Toaster This is a premium toaster!!  You can exactly control the shade of toast you desire.  It also works well with pop tarts, bagel, etc.'),
(5009, 12, 1, 4, '2014-04-12', 'Really enjoying toaster and broiler oven perfect BLT maker Nice little addition to kitchen. Use the broiler oven to cook bacon on tray  with tin foil. Switch to toaster and toast bagel. There is a cancel button if you need to pop toast early. Very pleased to replace a perfectly good toaster with this multi use appliance.'),
(5010, 5, 1, 4, '2014-06-10', 'After FIVE different Coffee Makers...... This one appears to be THE ONE!  Previous coffee makers I tried had the following issues: - Leaked during \"brew pause\" - Difficult to read display - Complex programming functionality - Difficult to fill with water - Coffee was not hot enough - Water left over after brewing cycle complete. With this Ham Beach, none of the above issues are evident.  It appears to be well built and well designed for a $50.00.  Each cup of coffee is better than the last.  Favorites things about the 46201 are the removable water tank, Easy to read display, and push button & swiveling coffee housing.  It is also quite a bit smaller than my previous coffee maker which is a plus for me.'),
(5011, 7, 3, 5, '2016-02-21', 'Purchased the coffee maker 3 weeks ago.I have used it everyday.It\'s a lovely machine,coffee is nice and hot and the price was a real treat.'),
(5012, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-14', 'Amazing Economic Toaster Oven I love this toaster oven, the Even Toast Technology(yes that\'s a thing) spreads the heat all over the oven. My only con is that is heats up really fast so Pay Attention.'),
(5013, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-22', 'Five Stars This is a great toaster. Unless you want to spend over $100. Very happy with my purchase.'),
(5014, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-23', 'love. my new oven works pderfectly Oven meets and exceeds my expectations'),
(5015, 11, 1, 2, '2014-03-25', 'smoke comes out sides of the glass door while toasting I turn on the nearby oven fan so the smoke detector won\'t go off while toasting because smoke comes out the sides of the door. If you are using the toaster again immediately after finishing, be sure to put it on a lower setting or the next piece will be burnt.'),
(5016, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-19', 'Five Stars Cooks food quickly and efficient.'),
(5017, 8, 1, 5, '2014-03-22', 'Black & Decker Coffee maker DCM 600W  5 cup drip I have viewed ratings on this product and I am  satisfied  that  I did purchased this product. I can always relied on the status of  the product  of its departure  and  arrival. It is exactly what I was looking for.As always I am pleased with the service.'),
(5018, 10, 1, 2, '2015-02-01', 'Bad product It was working perfectly at the beginning and then after some days, it was burned! It doesn\'t work anymore. I taught the product was very good...'),
(5019, 6, 1, 4, '2014-11-22', 'Good. Good cheap toaster.'),
(5020, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-18', 'Four Stars works great'),
(5021, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'Ingenius design Better than my Cuisinart toaster. Takes less space. Has wider access for English Muffins - if you use Wolferman\'s, (and I do) which are the thickest on the market. I read other comments that complained of the top closing device that it allowed heat to escape. Heat seems adequate to me.'),
(5022, 5, 1, 2, '2015-06-08', 'Buyer Beware - Unit Omits Essential Permanent Coffee Filter Buyer beware!  This unit comes with no permanent coffee filter, an optional assessory.  Using standard sized paper filters (#1), the grounds slip around the edge of the paper filter and down into the brewed coffee.  Don\'t know if #2 paper filter size would do the trick but thats not available at the local shopping stores here. I give this item as poor rating due to my perception that sleazy marketing is going on here.  The unit as priced omits an essential assessory (the permanent filter).  The real cost is $9 more plus shipping for a assessory that probably costs 50 cents to manufacture.  A reputable manufacure (in my opinion) would be up front on this hidden cost.'),
(5023, 11, 1, 2, '2014-06-30', 'Burns everything - take your money elsewhere I purchased this toaster oven above all the other ones because 1) it was the most highly rate toaster oven and 2) it was Amazon\'s #1 best seller. I bought it with high expectations but after having it for a few weeks, I ended up sending it back. It literally burn eeevvveeerrryyyttthhhiiinnnggg. Didn\'t matter what setting it was on, it burnt everything. Too bad - it\'s a perfect little toaster oven! We purchased a Cuisinart instead - hoping it will out perform the B&D.'),
(5024, 4, 1, 2, '2016-05-02', 'Stopped working after 2 years First time writing a product review on Amazon. Wanted to warn people, look elsewhere. Worked well while it worked but only lasted two years. Doesn\'t even turn on. Unacceptable to me. How hard can it be to design a toaster oven that lasts?'),
(5025, 2, 1, 2, '2015-02-27', '2_ stars: great if you like burnt toast I kinda have to wonder what sort of bread would require the \"dark\" setting in this toaster oven. I use sturdy wholegrain bread, thickly cut, and it took a lot of trial and error before I realized that I had to turn the knob to the lighter side of \"medium\" to prevent the toast from burning. Even so, the crust still gets black on the edges before the middle toasts. There\'s no sensor. Basically, it\'s just a timer with little toast icons on it to represent the \"settings.\" And speaking of the timer knob, to do anything in this machine you have to turn the knob past 10 minutes, then reverse it to your desired time/setting. It\'s a perfect irritant for a bad rotator cuff.  As for the heating mode, the oven temperatures seem to run very hot. And the little heating tray is flimsy and difficult to clean. Maybe I\'m expecting too much of a lower-cost toaster oven. I did a lot of research before I bought this one and didn\'t find one with better ratings.'),
(5026, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-07', 'Best coffee maker ever! Love it!  Great tasting coffee, easy to fill and brews fast!  I don\'t remove the reservoir and love the large opening at the top to fill it and doesn\'t spill out of the carafe even when pouring fast.  I use the medium setting for the warming plate and switch it to low when the pot is getting low... Every cup tastes as good as the first.  Have had it a little over a month and am very pleased!'),
(5027, 6, 1, 5, '2017-01-08', 'Great toaster! Just the right size and with the availability of several settings on the dial, toast and english muffins are coming out perfectly.  I don\'t see how it could be much better.'),
(5028, 6, 1, 3, '2015-04-21', 'It\'s okay for the price Toasts okay but tends to be uneven from side to side on the bread. I like the extra lift available in the slots to help get small pieces out without reaching in or finding some utensil to grab it.'),
(5029, 11, 1, 2, '2014-09-25', 'Disappointed with the toasting element Disappointed with the toasting element.  Never have I burned so much bread before trying to figure out the right setting'),
(5030, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-12', 'Worked for very short time... The k-cups wouldn\'t work & when they did, brewed a very light color. I contacted HB & this is what they said. During the development of these models, we conducted extensive testing on a very large number of different K-cups. We have found that there is a significant variability in the K-cup manufacturing process which causes some types of K-cups to be weaker at the seams where the foil on the top of the K-cup is fused to the plastic cup. We recommend using Green Mountain or Great Value brand K-cups. Never said anywhere that only those 2 brands could be used, I returned to Walmart & will never buy HB product again. GO KEURIG.'),
(5031, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-20', 'I really like this coffee maker I really like this coffee maker! The little wheels on the bottom make this easy to pull out to fill then put back into place. I can adjust the brewing strength to suit whichever coffee I use and the swing out basket operates with a simple press of a button. Very glad I made this purchase. Update 7/4/2015:  I just discovered that this coffee maker is NOT \"early morning, I\'m not awake, crap I forgot to get the coffee ready\" foolproof. Most coffee makers I\'ve owned won\'t actually make the coffee if you don\'t put the carafe in it\'s proper place - this one does ;-(. I do use one of those  permanent gold filter things...don\'t know if that makes a difference or not. I still recommend this coffee maker, I think it\'s great - just not fool proof...lol'),
(5032, 3, 1, 5, '2015-10-21', 'Great appliance Love it. Use it all the time.'),
(5033, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Five Stars very good even toasting.'),
(5034, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-22', 'Five Stars Great!'),
(5035, 6, 1, 2, '2015-01-22', 'Didn\'t toast evenly I\'ve had this quite a while now and like many of the features. The one major issue I have is that it doesn\'t toast evenly on both sides. It seemed fine in the beginning, but soon after one side would toast more than the other...very bothersome. And, this is for both slots! The removable crumb tray is good to have, and being able to push up the lever to raise the bread higher after it finished toasting is nice. For the price it should have toasted better - that\'s why only 2 stars. I\'ve learned to live with it and will wait for it to die before getting a new toaster. My last Cuisinart toaster (a 4 slicer) lasted many years.'),
(5036, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'LOVE IT!!!!! I bought this for fathers day and my husband loves it... So do I :) it\'s the best coffee maker I\'ve purchased. Thanks, keurig, for the free pods for this review..'),
(5037, 12, 1, 1, '2016-02-16', 'The lever spring broke down after 3 months\' use. The lever spring of the toaster broke down after only 3 months\' use. Very disappointed. Can I replace the item?'),
(5038, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-25', 'Love having this in my apartment Love having this in my apartment! It is quick and easy to use. Definitely recommend! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5039, 8, 1, 5, '2014-09-14', 'Five Stars Awesome'),
(5040, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-14', 'I love this item I love this item!!! Great for one serving shakes. You must be very careful at times or it will over flow.'),
(5041, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-20', 'Toaster Oven Love this toaster oven. I\'ve had others that were more expensive and were bigger, taking up too much counter space. This one works well and doesn\'t look too big on the counter.'),
(5042, 5, 1, 3, '2016-05-26', 'I like it hot enough to sip Though it has 3 heat settings, even the hottest is not hot enough.  I like it hot enough to sip.  Also I want to be able to set the automatic time off.  Two hours is not enough.  Also I have not found a way to remove lid from the glass pot.  So I cannot put it in dishwasher.  But even with these 3 things I don\'t like, it still is much better than some pots that are more expensive.  I do like the fact I can remove the water tank.  That it is seamless, can be washed, and will not be as likely to leak as the tanks have on at least 2 other coffee pots I\'ve owned.'),
(5043, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-06', 'Hamiltion Beach is a quailty company... Bought this as a gift for my sister, who is a big Hamilton Beach fan.  She had a similar one, made by Hamilton Beach, for YEARS!  I thought she needed an upgrade so, I got her this.  She refuses to part with the original one!  She now has two, she loves them both!!'),
(5044, 11, 1, 4, '2014-11-20', 'Just fine, with a knob design I\'d change It\'s a fine oven. I wouldn\'t say it\'s amazing but it does what you expect. The design of the knobs is a bit weird. The lower knob, when turned all the way to the left, puts the oven \"always on.\" To me, this isn\'t intuitive. It seems there is a better way to lay out the knob positioning.'),
(5045, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-13', 'Best designed coffee maker for convenience and easy use we have ever owned! We have owned many coffee makers over the years. Its been disappointing how poorly designed many have been for the user. This is the best coffee maker for everyday use we have owned. The coffee loads from the front, the water storage unit is detachable so it be refilled at the sink and the programming process for automatic brewing is more intuitive than any other machine we have used. It is easy to see why it received the highest user ratings on Amazon. Highly recommended based on our first week of use!'),
(5046, 3, 1, 4, '2016-03-15', 'Four Stars Came in perfect condition. Absolutely love it!'),
(5047, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-09', 'LEAVE IT WITH THE TOASTER I\'m giving this toaster with a five star rating! It easy to use and easy to clean. My husband gave this to me as a gift last year and up until today I\'m using it to heat hotdogs, chickens and pork. It heats everything so fast! That\'s why, I suggest if you\'re looking for the perfect toaster, buy this one!'),
(5048, 1, 1, 1, '2016-07-20', 'KEURIG: If You Really Don\'t Like Coffee Time to write an updated - but not changed - review. Albert Einstein once remarked that \"perfection of means and confusion of end characterize our age\". Keurig has perfected the means ( convenient technology ) to produce a consistently mediocre end ( a nearly tasteless cup of \"coffee\". ) No one - no matter what coffee you use, including your own - can produce a decent hot beverage resembling properly brewed coffee using these machines. Lord knows, I\'ve tried. So, if you value convenience above all else, buy one of these contraptions. If you actually like the taste of coffee, get some green coffee beans, a nice little home roaster, a burr grinder, and a pour-over funnel, and make the real thing.'),
(5049, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-14', 'Love it. Love our new coffee maker.'),
(5050, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-25', 'Awesome machine!! I LOVE my new Kerig! I\'ve been a part of the Kerig family for a couple years, but this machine surpassed my expectations! I love the color! Looks so much better than a big black machine in my counter. The new shape of the machine is also pleasing to the eye! If recommend this machine to any avid coffee drinker!'),
(5051, 4, 1, 5, '2016-03-06', 'Five Stars works great, perfect size.'),
(5052, 3, 1, 5, '2015-04-19', 'Easy to operate and maintain does all as advertised. Would buy again if i had to. Easy to operate and maintain.'),
(5053, 3, 1, 2, '2015-11-21', 'Two Stars Doesn\'t well.  Uneven heating'),
(5054, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-28', 'great space saver in my little kitchen use it all the time... great space saver in my little kitchen...'),
(5055, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-15', 'One Star Terrible setting knobs..... Barely able to see'),
(5056, 7, 3, 2, '2016-05-10', 'Only used the coffee ground. It spirted at beginning and end all over the place. Returned.'),
(5057, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-28', 'great toaster Our old toaster went bad on a Saturday morning.  I went to Walmart and Target to check out their toasters and didn\'t find anything I liked.  Saturday afternoon I ordered this toaster.  It arrived Monday afternoon.  Amazing service.  I especially like how the handle allows you to lift up the toast to get it out.  And it is a cool touch.  That\'s what I was looking for.'),
(5058, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-07', 'I absolutely loved using it so much there that when I needed ... A local coffee shop has this toaster for the patrons to use with their bagels. I absolutely loved using it so much there that when I needed a new toaster of my own I immediately wanted this one. I\'ve had it for 5 months and it still works amazing.'),
(5059, 4, 1, 4, '2016-04-30', 'Four Stars Not fancy but suits me very well.'),
(5060, 7, 3, 5, '2016-08-07', 'I have had two Keurig\'s and this makes a better cup of coffee, it\'s a little slower but well worth the wait');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(5061, 6, 1, 2, '2014-09-15', 'Don\'t rely upon the name to purchase a toaster After quite a few months of use I really do not like this Cuisinart because of the lack of any control over the browning of toast.  While the toaster appears to be functioning (the filaments are all on), there is really a disconcerting degree of browness, going from a deep coloration on one side to nearly none on the opposite one.  And this is whether or not you are attempting to toast muffins or brown bread. I do like one of the functions, the lifting of the toasted article when it apparently done.  But, it is only so I can then switch the item so that it gets uniformly toasted - and have left it lower in order to double the toasting. It may be that Cuisinart is a relatively expensive article but it would be better for them to merchandise this toaster as something other than by the name of Cuisinart - which we expect to be first class.'),
(5062, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-20', 'Switched from being a Mr. Coffee fan We bought this coffee maker when our Mr. Coffee coffee maker died. We\'ve always had Mr. Coffee coffee makers, but I did a little looking around and saw this Hamilton Beach coffee maker got some great reviews, so I broke with tradition and got it. We really like the removable water reservoir and the pop-out filter - very handy! It is also nice that it has wheels on the bottom that spin, so you can easily turn the machine around on your counter. So far, I think we\'ve got a winner!'),
(5063, 6, 1, 3, '2015-03-30', 'Great toaster. This is a great toaster, especially for the price. It toasts evenly - not like my previous expensive toaster - had to flip the toast in that one because it only toasted on one side.'),
(5064, 4, 1, 2, '2016-04-15', 'Not fond of this toaster oven Not particularly happy with this toaster oven. I find that the toast burns no matter what setting I try. If I want to toast a baguette, the rack setting in the middle meant for toast burns the top and if I drop the rack down it burns the bottom. The beep that signals the toast is done also is so loud it sounds like a smoke alarm.'),
(5065, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-22', 'Fantastic machine! Love the red color! Works great especially for tea as the hot water is always ready and waiting.'),
(5066, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-02', 'Five Stars Works well, convenient size.'),
(5067, 2, 1, 3, '2015-12-28', 'Its okey, but.... I love the oven it self, but after using it for a month the surface of the metal pan started to peal, which makes food to stick to it. I am upset, but not only about that...when I toast my bread, it toast it unevenly  (closer to the walls it toast stronger then the middle.) In general I stil like it. I will try to call customer suport to see what\'s up with a pan.'),
(5068, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-23', 'Love it! Use it several times a week Love it!  Use it several times a week!'),
(5069, 4, 1, 1, '2015-06-15', 'too tinny and big not insulated too tinny  and big  not insulated enough'),
(5070, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-20', 'good drip coffee maker Makes a really good pot of coffee and it\'s quick and easy to fill and clean.  the carafe doesn\'t spill everywhere - which can be an issue for me in the mornings.  simple, but has all of the features i would use on a coffee maker.  I wouldn\'t call it small on the counter, but it is pretty compact for a 12 cup.  get the permanent filter basket for less trash.'),
(5071, 8, 1, 5, '2014-08-19', 'does a good small pot for older mom, works well, just on/off button no timer, does a good job'),
(5072, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Five Stars Toaster is designed well and made well.  Toasts any thickness of bread evenly as desired.'),
(5073, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-07', 'Learning to dial toast level correctly is a little tough ... Learning to dial toast level correctly is a little tough -- miss the older model with a push button for toast and separate dial for darkness. Whole rack wants to slide out whenever removing hot item. Okay value for the price, but I miss the older style.'),
(5074, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-27', 'love it. Fast brewing...love it.'),
(5075, 7, 3, 3, '2014-02-05', 'Excellent for single coffee'),
(5076, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(5077, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-22', 'Five Stars ,uy bien'),
(5078, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Adore this coffee make - best one I\'ve ever owned. I\'m not really one to gush about a coffee maker, however, I just had to write about how much I adore this one.  Everything about it is perfect.  It\'s easy to program, no manual needed.  I hate those coffee makers that have 20 steps just to program your coffee to brew at 6am.  This one is as simple as could be.  I love that the coffee pot is surrounded on the sides by the coffee maker - it seems to help keep the coffee piping hot.  I love that the coffee is piping hot.  I love the removable reservoir which makes filling the water so incredibly easy.  I love that the coffee doesn\'t spill when you pour it.  There is not a single thing about this coffee maker that I don\'t love.  I\'ve always used a Mr. Coffee so I was hesitant to try something new but, when my Mr. Coffee broke after only one year, I decided to try this one based on the positive reviews and I couldn\'t be happier.  Great coffee maker.'),
(5079, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-14', 'so good. i like the blue display so far, so good. i like the blue display. it makes seeing  things a lot easier than a previous one i had.'),
(5080, 6, 1, 2, '2015-01-25', 'Not all the coils heat up Not all of the coils in the heating panel heat up making for very uneven toast. Cuisinart (like many brands) seems to have sold their name to the lowest bidder. Also, I do not think this should be called \"compact\" because it is only a quarter-inch smaller than a normal toaster. There are some huge toasters out now but they should not set the standard.'),
(5081, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Good coffee maker I read the reviews before I bought this and most people complained about the gauge being incorrect, I have not had this problem or any other problem with this coffee maker. We are happy with it and have had it a month now.'),
(5082, 2, 1, 3, '2016-10-29', 'Three Stars Not as easy to use as the last B&D it replaced.'),
(5083, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-23', 'Five Stars Love not having to poor the water into the tank.  Easy coffeemaker to use, I like it.'),
(5084, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-29', 'Love it Powerful'),
(5085, 5, 1, 1, '2016-04-01', '... rarely write product reviews but this item was so bad I feel I don\'t have a choice I very very rarely write product reviews but this item was so bad I feel I don\'t have a choice.  I bought this for my son after lots of research.  He is moving into his own place and I loved the idea of the auto shut off.  He took it out of the box and used it the next day.  Being young he threw the box away immediately.  On the VERY FIRST USE the silver plate at the very top came off.  Next I found small black plastic chunks everywhere.  Once I got them all cleaned we tried one more use.  Then the rest of the silver front plate came off.  Since he had thrown all the packaging and receipts away I knew I couldn\'t return.  I literally just threw this money away.'),
(5086, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Perfect Works great. Does not drip or spill when pouring, which was my main complaint about my last coffee maker. Pour spout was terrible. This one is a dream. Brews great coffee with no mess!'),
(5087, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-21', 'Great Coffee Machine! We\'ve had this coffeemaker for 6 month now and still love, love, love it. Love the single cup pouring. Due to artritus, I am unable to lift the full cherrif so the one cup pouring is fantanstic. My only hope is that Cuisinart will not discontinue this for a long, long time.'),
(5088, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-22', 'Very nice toaster oven I love this Toaster oven.  It is replacing a Black and Decker toaster oven I bought in 2001, that has just started giving me problems.  It was just wore out, I use it all the time.  This new one is much nicer and works much better than my old one, and the price is the same as I paid for my old one.  Quality went up and the price stayed the same, excellent!  Makes perfect toast and grills my sandwiches to perfection.  The timer knob takes some getting used too, it annoyed me at first but I like it now, it works great.  And I\'m so glad they are still making a more compact model like this one.  This model is the perfect size for counter top, in my opinion.'),
(5089, 6, 1, 4, '2016-11-01', 'Great product. What can I say? It\'s a toaster and it does what it\'s suppose to do.'),
(5090, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-02', 'It works great! At first it does have a weird smell It works great!  At first it does have a weird smell, but the product tastes fine in the end.  It does a wonderful job of mixing smoothies.'),
(5091, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-12', 'Five Stars Great product!!!!'),
(5092, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-06', 'Love the removable water reservoir There is nothing about this coffee maker that I don\'t love! The taste, the wheels, the heat feature, being able to fill it from the sink, the coffee basket at the touch of a button, the look with my stainless appliances. A perfect coffee maker!'),
(5093, 11, 1, 3, '2014-10-12', 'Not All Expected! Smaller than expected. Bad for doing hash browns!'),
(5094, 4, 1, 3, '2015-08-03', 'Heating element failed supernova-style just before(!!!) the (3-year) warranty expired I wrote a question-answer elsewhere, but the short if it is that mine failed just inside the 3-year warranty period.  The bottom heating element failed (like so many of the others) catastrophically and now neither of the lower elements work. Because I\'m a California resident (see our \"special\" section on the warranty page of the user\'s manual), I can supposedly take it back to any local Cuisinart retailer and get a replacement at no cost, or send it back at the manufacturer\'s expense for them to deal with. Except for the practically unintelligible printing on the controls on the front panel, I otherwise liked this product while it worked.  Hopefully they\'ve found a new source of heating elements since 2012, but I probably wouldn\'t take a chance on this model unless I knew this to be true.  That is, unless dealing with warranty claims is a hobby of yours and  you still have 20-20 vision to read the panel markings. EDIT: Just got back from BedBathAndBeyond with my new TOB-40 that I got exchanged (without too much discomfort) on the spot.  The packaging is new as well as the designs of the pan (moreso) and the slide-in rack (lessso).  The panel labeling hasn\'t changed since 2012, unfortunately.  The other notable changes are the (already) short power cord is now even shorter and there\'s a new non-metallic lip on the top edge of the door that lessens the opportunities for burning your fingers when opening the oven.  I seem not to have gotten a flimsy raised rack which fit inside the tray which may have come with the 2012 unit (although it may have been an appendage from its short-lived Oster predecessor oven). It remains to be seen if the overwhelming weakness of this oven, the medium/long-term reliability of the heating elements, has been remedied or not.  Only time will tell.'),
(5095, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-10', 'Not bad Keurig! I really really enjoy most of the upgrades on this new brewer.  The giant reservoir is awesome.  The needle cleaning tool has already come in handy.  It is so much quieter than my old one. My main complaint is that some of my Keurig K-cups that do not have the white ring on the top are not usable despite being authentic.  There are a few third party brews that I really enjoy and can no longer use as well.  The clearance on this one is a little lower than my older one, my favorite mug no longer works.  I have an easy fix though, just pull out the drip tray for a second and pop back on when I\'m done. I received this product complimentary for testing purposes, all opinions are my own.'),
(5096, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-22', 'Awesome! Use to have a Hamilton Beach Brewstation, which is really not a bad choice, but this one is really the winner. Easier to use, makes great coffee and the machine looks really high quality'),
(5097, 11, 1, 3, '2014-03-13', 'Barely \"okay\" The directions were not really clear and the dials on the toaster are very hard to read.  I\'ve had it for a while and still am having trouble figuring out where to place the dial to get the kind of toast level I want.  Don\'t dare try anything else!  Also it doesn\'t seem too substantial.  I needed a smaller size toaster and this when seemed to fit the bill.  However, I now wish I looked/shopped more.'),
(5098, 2, 1, 1, '2016-08-20', 'I am really disappointed It burns the toast even when it\'s set right ... I am really disappointed It burns the toast even when it\'s set right and its metal is cheep quality.'),
(5099, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-26', 'Good'),
(5100, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-30', 'Love it! This is an amazing machine. I love how you can make a delicious cup of coffee or brew a while carafe when you have company over. The only thing I don\'t like is having to hold down the button to dispense hot water.'),
(5101, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'MY WIFE SAYS FANTASTIC.. I DON\'T DRINK COFFEE BUT LIPTON TEA ... MY WIFE SAYS FANTASTIC..I DON\'T DRINK COFFEE BUT LIPTON TEA AND HOT CHOCOLTE AR MY BAG...THANKS FOR A GOOD SYSTEM..'),
(5102, 5, 1, 5, '2016-06-13', 'but so far I really like it. It\'s easy to fill I\'ve only had the coffeemaker about 1 month, but so far I really like it.  It\'s easy to fill, since you take the water well from the maker and hold it under the faucet.  It\'s also easy to remove the coffee basket for cleaning.  The coffee is hot and the warner keeps it hot.  It it continues to work well, I will be very happy with it.'),
(5103, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-16', 'Good looking and spacious interior Simpler than most toaster ovens today. Good looking and spacious interior.'),
(5104, 8, 1, 3, '2016-09-14', 'Three Stars On the third day it stops working... Don\'t know why.'),
(5105, 6, 1, 1, '2015-10-01', 'Zero Stars Less than three months after purchase, this toaster (while being used exactly as specified) started a large fire in our kitchen. All the heating elements on the right side (both slots) channeled into one set of coils (the extreme right) and were so hot (toaster on level 3, not defrost) on a single piece of bread, that the bread started on fire, shooting flames over a foot in the air. It is only by luck that I was nearby, and the toaster was in an open area of the kitchen, that I was able to put the flames out without damage to our kitchen or home.  This toaster is dangerously malfunctioning and should be redesigned and taken off the market until fixed. Update: THIS PROBLEM HAS YET TO BE RESOLVED BY THE CUSTOMER SERVICE AS OF ONE FULL MONTH POST-FIRE.'),
(5106, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-29', 'Updates doesn\'t mean its better Preferred my old one.  This is attractive but is very noisy and the water reservoir is in the back, made of light plastic with a flimsy lid.  This model only goes up to 12.oz. I knew I wouldn\'t use the options on the other models so I purchased this one.  I do enjoy all their products and I received the brewer with 2 days, beautifully packaged.  Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5107, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-03', 'Great appliance!! Excellent little oven and toaster for the price.'),
(5108, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Five Stars What I like about this toaster is you can shut it off so it doesn\'t burn the toast.'),
(5109, 5, 1, 3, '2014-03-06', 'Not quite what I expected The coffee maker works well. We like the timer and the removable water reservoir. It is not complicated to use. We bought the coffee maker hoping we could keep it in one spot on the counter top underneath the cabinets. Hamilton Beach promotes this as having a swivel base. I took it as it had a stationary base plate and it was on a carousel type set-up. It is actually 4 little rollers on the bottom of the entire unit. So the whole thing rotates. The biggest problem is that it has a vent at the top of the unit. When the coffee finishes brewing it emits a tremendous amount of steam which, over time, could warp the bottom of the cabinets and ruin our under cabinet lights. So when we make coffee we pick up the coffee maker and pull it out from under the cabinet. Not sure if I would have bought it know this up front.'),
(5110, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Love it Love this toaster so far'),
(5111, 6, 1, 3, '2015-03-29', 'Some one make a grat toaster please! It is still working after 4 months. I have to press the lever twice sometimes to get the bread to start toasting. The spring mechanism is not that great, which I knew when I got it from reading on line. Come on , this is not rocket science, and it isn\'t A Lexus....Can\'t someone come up with a decent toaster...like the one my parents had for 40 years, but energy efficient of course.'),
(5112, 6, 1, 1, '2016-03-10', '... an Amazon review before but this item is so bad that I feel compelled I have never written an Amazon review before but this item is so bad that I feel compelled. Plus I bought this because of all the positively glowing reviews on here. Many reviewers must be getting some kind of kick-backs or incentives. There\'s no way people actually really like this toaster. One thing I can say is that you never know what kind of toast you will get. Doesn\'t matter what setting you use. Sometimes burnt, sometimes completely underdone, many times the two sides come out toasted completely differently. If you enjoy never knowing what will happen when you pop your bread in the toaster, then get this product. You will love it.'),
(5113, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-06', 'Five Stars Love it!!!.'),
(5114, 1, 1, 1, '2016-02-01', 'Buyer Beware!! Very very disappointed that this lovely little machine that has so many admirable features will NOT allow me to use my favorite K-cups (San Francisco Fog Chaser).  I brought it home very excited, had gotten a great deal at it at a local store (sorry, not Amazon for a change), and after reading and following instructions, the info screen told me that the cup I\'d put in could not be used.  Unaccepable! I realize there are hundreds of varieties that it will support, but I\'m a big fan of San Francisco Fog Chaser and buy it in bulk and am unwilling to change.  Back to the store we go!'),
(5115, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', 'Five Stars good.'),
(5116, 3, 1, 4, '2015-03-28', 'I feel like Goldielocks when it comes to toaster ovens the past ... I feel like Goldielocks when it comes to toaster ovens the past few months! I had a Cuisenart Toaster oven for 5 years-it was the second one-the first one lasted 7 years!  However they don\'t offer that particular style any more, which sucks. I first ordered a Breville convection.  It was HUGE-much too big for my studio kitchen area.  Sent that back and ordered a little Panasonic which was the absolute mini toaster oven.  After burning my cookies for the second time, I decided to find a more traditional toaster oven. While this is really too large, it isn\'t as big as the Breville however and the price is super.  It has a pizza bump out, bakes cookies (I make \'special\' cookies and need a temp control!)  It comes with 4 rack positions and fully adjustable presets. Included  is a pan for broiling which works nicely.  The crumb tray removes from the FRONT!! a Great Feature in my opinion.  I lined both the crumb tray and broiler pan with oven liners that help with clean up-I wish I\'d known about them before.  The convection feature takes a bit to get to get used to but the suggestion to drop the temperature by 25 degrees helped not overcook the things I use it for. Frozen pizza, bagels, regular toast all came out perfectly.  Tonight I baked teriyaki chicken breasts and red potatoes-the oven is big enough for 2 small pyrex / corning ware style containers which makes cooking different things easy. I don\'t love this as much as my Cuisenart one but it\'s nice and practical for most things.'),
(5117, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-06', 'It is exactly as described. I followed all instructions ... It is exactly as described. I followed all instructions prior to using, there was no leaking, no plastic taste and the cord was the same length as other coffe makers I have owned previous.'),
(5118, 2, 1, 2, '2016-01-16', 'Terrible at toast The timer (which is the mechanism you use to turn this toaster oven on, for all modes) is really not user friendly. Following the instruction manual, I tried several times, but was never able to get toast consistently to come out between warm or burned. I had to manually twist the timer back to shut it off to achieve results I would call enjoyable toast. I don\'t want to have to monitor the toaster to get it to toast properly. I am very disappointed with this on a basic level; it may work fine for baking small items or reheating, but if you plan on using a toaster oven frequently for toast, tI would recommend seeking another product.'),
(5119, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-23', 'It looks nice, it\'s easy to use and it makes quality coffee that doesn\'t burn on the way down. This is a very nice looking coffee machine. There are rollers on the bottom so you can pulled forward and back with ease along with rotating it to access the container that you put your water into. This container can be removed, so you can easily fill it at the sink or you can flip the lid and use the coffee pot to pour water into it. There are numbers on the side so you can measure how many cups of water you wish to add. This coffee machine should fit under any standard cupboard, with room to flip the lid for the water container. The display is nice and bright, the settings are easy to read, and it\'s pretty simple to program if you want your coffee read for you in the morning. There are several temperature settings for the heat plate that keeps your coffee warm while it sits in the pot. There is an automatic shutoff in case you forget to turn it off. The temperature of the coffee seems to be just what I like. I don\'t burn my lips drinking it right out of the pot. Right under the display, and right above the coffee pot, is the area that swings out so you can add your coffee grounds. The pot has a no drip feature which works quite well. Overall, after a years worth of uses, it\'s still working as intended. The only drawbacks so far have been the front plate around the display comes a bit loose, it pops up and can easily be popped back into place. And the numbers on the side of the water container have rubbed off in certain spots. Other than that, I have been very happy.'),
(5120, 6, 1, 3, '2015-07-14', 'A nice appliance It looks neat and is easy to use. We like the fact that there is a button to push, when using a frozen slice of bread, to prepare the bread for toasting.'),
(5121, 9, 1, 4, '2016-10-19', 'Does the cord seem too short?  Read on... First of all - we have been using the earlier version of this particular coffee maker for OVER FOUR YEARS and have loved it.  It explains in the manual that when you see the \"Clean\" light blinking, to follow the cleaning instructions with vinegar and water.  We have done that faithfully and that machine lasted longer for us than any other coffee pot we have ever owned!  (ps, the old machine had a normal cord that was not stuffed inside the machine) Just recently, our machine has needed cleaned much more frequently than usual - so in an effort to avoid being caught high and dry, we got on amazon and purchased the same machine, but new for $90.  When I pulled it out of the box, the cord was only sticking out about 4 inches.  It didn\'t seem to want to come out any further, and I was scared I would hyper-extend it.  Then I read in the manual that it has a short cord for safety and that you can use an extension cord if it\'s not long enough.  Well, I was pretty frustrated with this because I really didn\'t want to use an extension cord!!  So, I you-tubed the machine and read the question/answer on amazon and apparently I\'m not alone in my plight. THE ACTUAL CORD IS ABOUT 20 INCHES LONG, but it is just folded up inside the base.  It doesn\'t like to pull out very easily, so I kinda had to sit an jerk on it and jimmy it for awhile before I got enough out to be able to use it.  Poor designing, in my opinion, but if you know what\'s up and get that taken care of ... That first model was an excellent coffee maker and again, that one served us for over 4 years.  Hoping for the same performance from this one!.'),
(5122, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-11', 'If you are looking for a great coffee pot at a great price on Amazon then ... If you are looking for a great coffee pot at a great price on Amazon then this is it! I have gotten so many compliments on this that I have several friends who purchased it as well! I\'m so glad I bought this on Amazon because it\'s triple the price at other stores. This was well worth the money, it works great and doesn\'t burn your coffee. Be aware though that if you have low cabinets you have to move it to add the coffee and filter which doesn\'t bother me.'),
(5123, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-13', 'Five Stars We love it'),
(5124, 9, 1, 1, '2015-06-22', 'Continually breaks. I have been through 2 units. ... Continually breaks.  I have been through 2 units.  The first leaked at the dispenser and the unit was replaced without charge but after a few months the second unit won\'t brew. Keeps getting stuck and you have to turn on and off.  I have cleaned and purchased new filters but the \"Clean Light\" gets stuck and shuts off'),
(5125, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-06', 'Five Stars Great toaster oven.'),
(5126, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-24', 'Great Brewer!! After years of using a standard pot, my love for coffee had dwindled substantially, and I was to the point that I really no longer enjoyed drinking it. One day while at work, a coworker gave me a k-cup to use in the break room brewer. It was delicious, and I knew I HAD to have my own Keurig! I shop online a lot, and user reviews play a huge role in my decision making process. Most brewers had mixed reviews, but the Keurig 2.0 K200 seemed to have the most overall customer satisfaction. I liked the included water filter, as well as the cup or carafe option. When a local retailer had a sale plus gift card offer for this model, I took the plunge. BEST.DECISION.EVER. I love this coffeemaker! I\'ve owned my Keurig for about a month now, and I haven\'t experienced anything but total and complete satisfaction. There have been no issues, only fresh, flavorful coffee on demand. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5127, 1, 1, 1, '2016-05-23', 'WORTHLESS IF IT DOESN\'T TAKE ALL K CUPS Piece of Crap, doesn\'t take ALL K-Cups, only some of them...... This is where Keurig lost me. Either make a k cup unit that takes ALL kcups or don\'t. But please don\'t start making Keurig units that won\'t take all kcups after getting us all hooked on the kcup lifestyle........'),
(5128, 5, 1, 1, '2016-11-28', 'Electrical relay power malfunction after 2 weeks After about 2 weeks there was an electrical malfunction and a relay was tripping the power off randomly, without notice or evident cause.  I\'ve tried many different outlets and varying water levels, and the relay continues to trip the power to the machine off.'),
(5129, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-28', 'I am just so pleased with our new Hamilton Beach Single-Serve Coffee Maker!! On the weekends I make a full pot of coffee for my husband in the morning, but on work days, he always just waited until he arrived at work for his first cup of the day. Now that we have this little single serve, he can have one cup before he leaves for work and that gets his day off to a great start. I\'m not a big coffee drinker, but this is just so quick and handy, I find myself fixing a cup for me during the morning when before I wouldn\'t have bothered making a pot just for me. It\'s very fast and easy and since I don\'t like my coffee very strong, I just use a very small amount (around a teaspoon full), fill my favorite \"tea rose\" cup with water, dump in the coffee maker and in less than 3 minutes have a great cup of coffee. It\'s very easy to clean and I love not having to wash out a coffee pot. Just dump the grounds, toss the very few used grounds in the garbage, rinse the little basket and I\'m done. Couldn\'t be more pleased!!!'),
(5130, 3, 1, 4, '2015-08-23', 'I love all the features This thing is MASSIVE. I have a small apartment with full size appliances. I just wanted a toaster oven for toast and small things, so I don\'t heat up the place with the oven. I think this is for ppl who don\'t have an oven. I love all the features. I just wish it was smaller'),
(5131, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-20', 'Very happy with this Very happy with this.  We have many family members visit and my husband drinks decaf and not many family members do so having this helps with not having to make several pots of coffee.'),
(5132, 12, 1, 4, '2016-02-01', 'great little toaste-oven combo I really like the design of this toaster/oven.  It\'s small, fits well on my counter, and how nifty to have a toaster oven with a real toaster that makes good toast!  I\'ve only had it a few weeks, but so far, so good.  I\'d give it 5 starts except that there is no way to automatically shut off the oven component -- that\'s dangerous.  Also, be warned:  the period during which it outgasses a horrible burnt-plastic smell is much longer than just the \"first use\" that the directions mention.  I ended up putting it in a spare room to turn on repeatedly before the smell went away and I could bring it back into the kitchen.'),
(5133, 5, 1, 3, '2015-02-04', 'Planned Obsolescence Well, planned obsolescence is alive and well.  I had this coffee maker one year and five months before the switch broke and wouldn\'t turn on.  I\'m looking at it sitting in the garbage can as I type.  Just another piece of junk made in China that\'s designed to bust so you have to buy another one.  Luckily, I had a coffee press and avoided a caffeine withdrawal and associated headache this morning.  I\'ve got a $10 credit at Goodwill, so I\'ll be heading there today.'),
(5134, 3, 1, 3, '2016-03-29', 'My BLACK \'N\' DECKER product received today only had one ... My BLACK \'N\' DECKER product received today only had one of the four rubber feet for the bottom of the machine. We checked and doubled checked in the boxes and there were no more rubber feet. How do we get replacements?'),
(5135, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'ok I love this lil blender ok I love this lil blender!! the convenience, for this price I am completely happy about this purchase and the preciseness it provides for my day to day smoothies. I am going to buy my mom and sisters one as well'),
(5136, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'I Love It! I love, love, love my toaster best thing I ever brought.'),
(5137, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-01', 'Five Stars Perfect for my dorm room. No problems with blending, super nice that it has a removable cup'),
(5138, 5, 1, 3, '2016-09-23', 'Good coffee, poor fabrication I like this coffee maker, but the clock face fell off the second time I used it. Sigh.'),
(5139, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-19', 'Five Stars really pretty good'),
(5140, 10, 1, 3, '2015-03-13', 'Not worth the money. Go somewhere else! Worked great at first, but now it sounds like it\'s dying. Doesn\'t blend frozen fruit, or really anything at all.'),
(5141, 3, 1, 1, '2016-06-09', 'Attention I dont like it, l need returned label for it. Please send it to me.'),
(5142, 2, 1, 1, '2015-04-21', 'Terrible?? When it hot to 450 handle just come off because it screw in the plastic part. Terrible ?????'),
(5143, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-22', 'Love love! No more heating up the big oven! My kids heat up Totino\'s pizzas all the time in this plus other easy foods without using the big oven. My girls are finally taking the initiative to earn to cook!'),
(5144, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-24', 'An Improvement Over v1 In All Ways Except The Restrictions And Up-Sells We had a v1 Keurig brewer, and used it frequently. This new design is a step up in most ways! The touch screen is a bit of a novelty, but is attractive and gives messages you didn\'t see with the old version (which had no screen, just buttons). The unit is thinner and the loading mechanism is a better design, opening more forward than up, which means it can squeeze in tighter spaces under kitchen cabinets. There are also extra features like the ability to brew a whole carafe vs. a single cup and the ability to have a filter for the water. Plus, the package comes with a lot of useful extras like sample K-Cups, a solution to clean the reservoir and a tool to maintain the interior needle! The only thing not to like about the package is all the extra ways the manufacturer now tries to milk a little more money out of the customer. The biggest money grab is related to the decision to try to restrict the brewer to allow only officially approved K-Cups. Luckily, hacks exist to use old K-Cups or the reusable K-Cups that you can load with your own tea and coffee. For those interested, just buy and you can circumvent the Keurig restriction. There are also a couple other attempts to wiggle into your wallet by enticing you to buy the official cleaning solution and water filters (which only last a few months). However, since both those up-sells are optional, I can\'t complain too much. In summary, I don\'t particularly like the new marketing tactics, but the 2.0 really is an improved brewer and our family will be happily using it over the v1 brewer from now on!'),
(5145, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-14', 'Five Stars Just right for my little apartment. The extra settings don\'t hurt, either; especially the reheat.'),
(5146, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-20', 'Five Stars Works really great'),
(5147, 3, 1, 5, '2014-11-06', 'Totally satisfied with both This is my second B&D oven. Bought the first one years ago. Totally satisfied with both. Easy to use.'),
(5148, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-03', 'Poor product by Cuisinart.  Thank you Amazon for allowing me to return it. Toasts unevenly, cooks pizza unevenly.  The feature where it pulls the rack out automatically is great, but when you slide it any more, it slides/falls even further and tips downwards.'),
(5149, 11, 1, 4, '2014-01-10', 'A Fine Product I like the new B &D toaster oven.  It produces toast the way I like it and thus far has done a fine job in baking & broiling.  I don\'t like the pan that comes with the unit but have replaced it with one that works better.  The original pan was poorly designed and flimsy.'),
(5150, 6, 1, 4, '2014-10-13', 'Works well, but sides may not be so even Works well and looks well on the kitchen counter. And It is also light weight. Clean lines and easy to keep clean. However, the toaster doesn\'t do the sides evenly, You may like to consider the following for a more even toast http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001ARQYRU/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B001ARQYRU&linkCode=as2&tag=hocivfd-20&linkId=JNJZSF5T466OKPSF'),
(5151, 5, 1, 2, '2015-10-22', 'Didn\'t even last a year! This coffee maker made decent, if not great, coffee. My complaint is that it suddenly DIED on me after only 7 months, making it a terrible value. I had to run to the store and buy another coffee maker (NOT A HAMILTON BEACH!) when I really didn\'t have time and really wasn\'t expecting to have to replace the coffeemaker I had so carefully researched and chosen just months ago. Arg!'),
(5152, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-06', 'BEST TOASTER OVEN! My daughter saw mine and wanted one for herself so I gave it to her for Christmas. It replaced a larger toaster she had and gave her a small oven and took up less space.  I have had mine for greater than 5 years and it still works great.  I like it because I can do toast, English muffins or bagels and then use the oven for heating up pizza or making grilled cheese or tuna sandwiches.  It is easy to use.  One feature I love on it is the oven won\'t start heating until you slide the toaster mechanism which prevents the oven heat from escaping.'),
(5153, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-03', 'Long-lasting; well-built I bought this at least three years ago and use it about every month. The whole system still works as new.'),
(5154, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-23', 'Blending made ez Good product great price'),
(5155, 2, 1, 1, '2016-05-12', 'This toaster oven is a fire hazard. It get ... This toaster oven is a fire hazard. It get extremely hot to the touch on the outside--so much so that you have to use oven mitts to open it--and it does not always turn itself off when programmed. We are putting it in the trash and ordering a toaster from another brand. Amazon gave us a partial refund.'),
(5156, 7, 3, 4, '2015-11-29', 'I love my Flex Brew. It does allow a few coffee grounds to seep through, but I think it is probably the size of my grounds. It is not so bad that I\'m considering returning it. K-cups work wonderfully. I\'ve not had any messes that have needed cleaned and I\'ve used it at least 10 times in less than a week. It\'s a very good alternative to the $70+ dollars you\'d spend on other brands.'),
(5157, 6, 1, 1, '2015-06-22', 'Save your time & $$$$. - buy something else. Sending back !  One side of toast is dark, the other light.  One slice of (Arnold\'s) rye bread too long to fit in slot so you have to put it in so that part is just about sticking out of the top of the toaster - and that\'s not a long piece of bread.  Very poor design.'),
(5158, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-18', 'We use this bad boy up at the office and it\'s great We use this bad boy up at the office and it\'s great.  My office manager warms up her bagels every morning in it.'),
(5159, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-09', 'Five Stars Perfect for 4 slices of toast. Also will cook small potatoes.'),
(5160, 12, 1, 1, '2015-06-15', 'Slowly broke down This product worked well for a few days and then it slowly started to break down. First the door would not close properly or all the way. Second the tray would not slide in and out smoothly, you had to wiggle it to get to move. Next the toaster would not toast the slices evenly or the slices of toast would fall out of the slot and end up stuck in the back of the toaster. Lastly the lever to the toaster broke, so you could no longer toast any toast. I should of contacted the seller immediately after having problems. By the time the product completely broke I was past the 30 day return or replace warranty. So, if you start to experience any problems with the toaster contact the seller right away, otherwise you could run the risk of your toaster not being covered under warranty.'),
(5161, 11, 1, 4, '2014-04-07', 'Makes a good little toaster This is good little toaster oven I bought it for the purpose of making toast and baking small item that don\'t require a lot of time and got great price.'),
(5162, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-24', 'Very satisfied with this coffee maker!! Makes coffee really fast! Here is my simple and to the point review :) The good things about it: 1. Heats up and delivers my whole pot of coffee almost just as quick as my past Keurig did for my one CUP of coffee! 2.Keeps my coffee nice and hot for a long time. 3.Does not have any weird burned plastic taste or smell to it. The bad things about it: 1. I only have one small thing that I think could be improved, and that is that a small amount of coffee will remain in the pot due to the spout of the coffee pot lid, but no real biggie at all. Love this coffee maker!'),
(5163, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-18', 'Five Stars Exactly what I needed!!'),
(5164, 2, 1, 1, '2015-09-29', 'Died after 9 months of usage. Died after 9 months of usage. Went to cook dinner in mine and came back after the timer went off. Food was still cold. The toaster was making arcing sounds that made it sound like it was going to burst into flames. This is the second Black and Decker kitchen product I have had die this year after only several months of usage. I will not be purchasing any more B&D products.'),
(5165, 4, 1, 2, '2016-04-30', 'Lasted two years so I gave it two stars. ... Lasted two years so I gave it two stars.  Other reviewers complained of defective heating elements, and I had the same experience.  The front element warped and finally split open, and the oven stopped working.  My last toaster oven lasted at least 10 years.'),
(5166, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-23', 'Best of Both Worlds Yes, I like my new Keurig 2.0 coffee brewer, I love being able to make a fresh cup as needed and not wasting a whole pot if I get busy. I am receiving free pods for this review but I assure you my comments are genuine. I did buy a carafe so I can have the best of both worlds!'),
(5167, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-31', 'Four Stars Nice compact toaster oven at a good price. Works fast and well for reheating pizzas.'),
(5168, 5, 1, 3, '2016-09-03', 'Decent but cheap After 3 weeks could not program due to a malfunctioning button.  Liked the water compartment.'),
(5169, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-31', 'What a mess! The opening on the lid does not seal. Liquid goes everywhere. Redesign the lid or add a lid without opening just for when blending.'),
(5170, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-27', 'This Blender Comes Highly Recommended! I used this item today and realized that I purchased it for under $20 back in 2012.  This blender has paid for itself many times over.  I started dieting early this year and in an effort to consume more protein, I make a protein shake once a day.  This blender has held up to continual use over the years and it does an excellent job blending my protein, almond milk and fruit.  So far its help me to lose 20 lbs.  An excellent buy!!'),
(5171, 5, 1, 5, '2014-08-09', 'Great machine. Good value. Great machine. Easy to use. Unless you want your coffee scalding hot, turn down the keep warm plate to lowest level.'),
(5172, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-07', 'Excellent product As always this product arrived on schedule. The delivery people are the greatest. The toaster oven is easy to use and operate. I like it very much and would definitely would recommend it.'),
(5173, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-14', 'Five Stars good'),
(5174, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-06', 'Works great! Chews up frozen and fresh fruit/vegetables with no ... Works great! Chews up frozen and fresh fruit/vegetables with no problem. Just be sure to use a bit more water than you think is necessary and this little guy will get the job done.'),
(5175, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-14', 'Five Stars A++++'),
(5176, 4, 1, 5, '2015-08-04', '... the options we were hoping for and we were pleased with the end results The oven provided all the options we were hoping for and we were pleased with the end results.'),
(5177, 4, 1, 2, '2016-03-09', 'I\'m so glad it stopped working The first time I broiled something (it does says \"broiler\") it smoked up the whole outside and would not get clean. I\'m so glad it stopped working; now I know what I DON\'T want in such a product.'),
(5178, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Bonding over Coffee! This was a gift for my mom for work. Her department is all cubicles and they were competing with another department that invested in a high grade espresso machine. Thought this would help her get her coffee fix. She took to work and was a hit! Small and compact but capable of brewing up to 10 cups or more a day. Great little machine! I have heard nothing but awesome reviews from my mom and her co-workers. Thru a simple coffee machine it has brought her department together.'),
(5179, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Five Stars Excellent product. Highly recommend it.'),
(5180, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-27', 'Five Stars not too great but the price is awsome'),
(5181, 11, 1, 4, '2014-01-09', 'works great This toaster works great, but I am not able to fit 4 slices of toast in it.  Perhaps the smaller wonder bread size would fit, but not today\'s present whole grain types.  The toaster is pretty small.  It toasts very quickly and has a \"stay on\" feature for baking.'),
(5182, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-06', 'sent to my mom and she said she likes the ... sent to my mom and she said she likes the white it matches her kitchen. She loves Cuisinart products, this replaces a 20 year old Cuisinart toaster.'),
(5183, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-10', 'Five Stars I just love this oven so much! Beautiful color, and functional just as needed. Thank you.'),
(5184, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-25', 'Still working great I bought this for my girlfriend for Christmas last year.  Eight months later, it is still running great.  The stainless steel makes it very easy to clean.  The digital timer on it is a great feature, allowing the coffee to begin brewing before your alarm clock goes off.  The coffeemaker doesn\'t leak and everything is still working well on it.'),
(5185, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-14', 'Five Stars I love how simple this product is.'),
(5186, 10, 1, 3, '2015-03-24', 'Not much power. Instructions say don\'t use with ice ... Not much power.  Instructions say don\'t use with ice.  Can\'t even mix crushed ice up well in a drink.'),
(5187, 5, 1, 4, '2015-11-08', 'I still like this coffee pot I\'ve had this for about a year now. So far, I still like this coffee pot, and in my opinion, for the price, it works just as well as the $100 ones. I like the separate water tank and the swing out filter basket. I also like rectangular profile and flat back. The inside of the decanter is a little hard to clean on the top because of the large plastic trim, but I think it also helps to prevent it from breakage or cracking. I don\'t know how to prevent the hot plate from being discolored though. It seems to happen with all my coffee pots.'),
(5188, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-24', 'Love this coffee brewing system Love my coffee pot. It\'s great. I can enjoy my  Blue Mountain Coffee even quicker now.'),
(5189, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-03', 'Good toast, fast I bought this specifically because it is billed as \"compact\" and it is small. I had bought a toaster oven and ditched my old 4-slice toaster, but the toaster oven (while great as an oven) is too slow at toasting. This is a really good toaster--makes excellent toast, browned evenly on both sides, and does it quickly. Added features such as \"reheat\" are nice, but the bottom line is, good toast fast.'),
(5190, 10, 1, 3, '2015-11-10', 'Mehh This is the perfect little blender for making protein shakes but this isn\'t very powerful at all. You\'d be better off spending and extra $30 and getting something that can actually handle crushing up ice.'),
(5191, 5, 1, 3, '2016-09-25', 'So close to pretty darn good. Easy to use. No-drip pot. No drip when pulling out a pot still getting filled. Nice shape. Good coffee. BUT. A week of use and the front face - the rectangular piece that surrounds the buttons - fell off. Close examination showed that the tiny parts that grip the studs were shattered - on both sides. The pot still works fine without the face - it just looks a little wierd and makes me wonder what\'s going to fall off or break next.'),
(5192, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-13', 'Nice Super small and cute. Heats up quick.'),
(5193, 3, 1, 3, '2014-09-14', 'Yep sure dose get hot on all sides. Yep, getting epically hot. Are old one that looked similar got hot to but nothing lik this. Otherwise dose seem to work fine though.'),
(5194, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', 'Meets All My Brewing Requirements Lots of great practical features.  Swivel wheels allow you to roll the coffee maker out front under a cupboard for easy access.  Temperature control, setting for bold and setting for 1-4 cups are all features I use.  Blue light display for time and feature settings are easy to see.  I have only had this coffee maker for one month but I am very pleased.'),
(5195, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Five Stars What I needed.'),
(5196, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-02', 'Five Stars works great, nice look'),
(5197, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-30', 'I like the individual adjustments for each 2-slice side This may be the ultimate 4-slice toaster. The slots are wide enough so that bagel slices fit them without a struggle. The toasting mechanism works as it should and heats up quickly and consistently. I like the individual adjustments for each 2-slice side. The unit is also compact for a 4-slice toaster and fits well on my countertop.'),
(5198, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-19', 'Versatile This oven is everything either my wife or I could want, with multiple opportunities to do what we want to warm or cook food.'),
(5199, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-16', 'Love the white and the sturdy toaster. Well made and good choices on the toasting times.'),
(5200, 12, 1, 4, '2017-01-26', 'Four Stars Good, but toast falls off track some times.'),
(5201, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-01', 'It is difficult to see where the nobs are. ... It is difficult to see where the nobs are. Is it on toast, bagel, bake, or broil? The same for the temperature. The indicator on the nob should be larger or a different color.'),
(5202, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-24', 'YEA This works so well...easy to clean...my husband was able to make himself a snack with a ton of mess...YEA!!!.'),
(5203, 3, 1, 1, '2014-01-04', 'piece of junk that worked for a few months we needed a toaster oven.  my husband insist that we get an upgrade too - a convection oven that fits the whole chicken in.  so we brought it at outlet store about a year ago.  so it lasted 6 months or so.  these two months, it quit working - it will be either shuts off after the temperature and time set, or like today, can\'t even input anything. what a waste of money.  if i could give it no star, it deserves negative stars.'),
(5204, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-05', 'Would highly recommend it. this product was everything and more I expected.  Would highly recommend it.'),
(5205, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-25', 'Large quantity of coffee This coffee pot worked great.  We replaced it with a K-cup coffee maker since we don\'t drink as much coffee, but this maker makes good coffee.'),
(5206, 8, 1, 4, '2016-08-03', 'Four Stars This coffee pot is great for one person. It does tend to drip. I am satisfied for the price.'),
(5207, 6, 1, 5, '2017-01-24', 'Good quality toaster Excellent toaster. I have used it every morning For over a year and no problems.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(5208, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-09', 'Five Stars THIS TOASTER IS GREAT!'),
(5209, 12, 1, 3, '2014-07-12', 'Three Stars doesn\'t toast evenly'),
(5210, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-27', 'I bought this coffee maker a couple of months ago (like to wait how I really like an item before making a review...) I thought coffee didn\'t taste the same at first, but I adjusted the amount of coffee I was using and now I wouldn\'t use anything else. I make just one cup at the time on most days, but it\'s also great for making a few cups, as it brews very quickly. I like the fact that you can use your own coffee with it.'),
(5211, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-23', 'Don\'t let negative reviews fool you! GREAT product! This is by far my favorite kitchen appliance. I\'ve never owned a Keurig before, but I\'ve always wanted one. I just received the Keurig K250 a few days ago (Orange Zest, SO cute!) and I\'m already in love. I was super super iffy about making this purchase because I read so many negative things about this model in reviews. But, honestly nothing I read is true. I\'m going to explain further. The number one complaint I read  about the new 2.0 systems is the DRM. Many ppl hate the fact that you can\'t use any K-Cup unless it has the approved seal. This was a huge reason why I wasn\'t going to buy 2.0 system.--But it\'s not a problem at all! They have SO many varieties and brands that are approved. I don\'t see me running into any issues when it comes to the DRM. If you seriously can\'t just use a brand that isn\'t Keurig brewed, but another brand coffee maker. Because honestly every brand I see at my local walmart, works in this Keurig. Another complaint was that you cannot brew your own ground coffee--wrong! If you buy one of the new filters (Eco-Fill, Eco-Carafe, etc) you can brew your own. I gave 4 stars because I don\'t like how the Keurig stays on at all times. There\'s a power button on the screen that doesn\'t do anything. I know I could just unplug it, but I\'m afraid to damage it. However, I\'m sure the bigger models have an auto on/off option. It\'s super fast, super quiet, and super convenient! The coffee comes out hot and delicious! and there is no mess to clean up afterwards:) I love how many coffee flavor options I have now. I\'m so excited to try them all.'),
(5212, 9, 1, 4, '2015-02-22', 'still like the maker i have had the coffee maker for about  17 months and it starting to leak ever where, while i really like how it makes coffee keeps it hot. The reason i bought it was i had one before an it lasted 4 years. Now looking again, but i will say that i make a lot of coffee some times up to 3 pots a day. so for that i got the 4 stars'),
(5213, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'I really like the sliding door to fill coffee My family loves it.  My wife now compliments my rich tasting coffee.  I have not told it is the bold brew feature of the Hamilton.  Would buy again if I need to.  I really like the sliding door to fill coffee.  And the no spill lid is excellent.  Love it!'),
(5214, 6, 1, 5, '2016-10-17', 'This is a great toaster. It actually toasts the bread This is a great toaster.  It actually toasts the bread.  No more warmed bread that they now call toast.  If you only toast one slice you need to turn it down.  Two slices require a higher number.  You will figure it out and I probably should buy another one before they stop making them.'),
(5215, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'Five Stars She likes it just fine.. works perfect..'),
(5216, 5, 1, 2, '2014-12-16', 'weak coffee Makes a very weak, watery tasting cup of coffee!  Disappointing!'),
(5217, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'Superb product Since I\'m rating this five stars, I obviously like it quite a bit. But I\'ll start with the drawbacks. There are two that I\'ve discovered: 1) The unit has a very short cord. You\'ll need counter space very close to an outlet. It may be that the short cord has prevented my house from burning down, but I\'d still prefer a longer cord. 2) The top of the unit does get rather hot. The front--the handle and the knobs--do not have any such problem. So those are the only two negatives I have to say about the unit. Neither is close to a deal breaker. For those wondering why one would want a toaster oven when there are microwaves and toasters around, I can report that I had the same questions. However, as I received this free to review it, I put those concerns aside and ordered the oven. I\'m extremely pleased that I did. I\'ve used it for several things and found it\'s superior to the microwave for many things. With the multiple settings and timer, I can set the oven to just the right setting and wait until I hear the ding. I know that my meal will be cooked through. I\'ve found that the fake meat patties (such as Boca burgers and a variety of \"chick\'n\" dishes) are well cooked, far better than in the microwave. Bread that is too thick for a toaster toasts nicely in this oven, and I\'ve made great garlic bread in this oven--far, far, far better than the same in a microwave. Pizza works nicely in this oven too, though it\'s about the same as in a microwave. For grilled cheese sandwiches, there\'s no comparison. This oven is far better than a microwave (though not as good as an actual grill, but that much is obvious in the name of the sandwich). I should note that the time it takes this oven to heat a meal is about three to four times the time it takes a microwave to heat the same meal, but that additional time is worth it for certain foods. And cleaning is easy. There\'s an easily removable crumb tray to catch drippings, and the baking tray itself (which is, I confess, a little bit smaller than it needs to be) washes easily. All in all, this little oven has been a great find, and it\'s getting far more use than I expected. I\'m very pleased with it.'),
(5218, 5, 1, 1, '2016-09-11', 'One Star This is the second time the product broke down within 2 months.'),
(5219, 10, 1, 4, '2015-06-02', 'Great item. I use mine for formula mixing (I have twins, so I have to make a larger amount of formula). I use it for my smoothies as well. Great item.'),
(5220, 7, 3, 5, '2015-02-12', 'A handy, quick and easy cup of coffee at any time. Versatile in cup sizes and coffee. Enjoyable appliance.'),
(5221, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-08', 'I\'ve been using the coffee maker for about a week or so and absolutely love it. It\'s ready to use right out of the box, and can be used with a coffee cup (using the included stand) or a travel mug. I really enjoy the flexibility of being able to either use ground coffee or k-cups. It doesn\'t take up much counter space and has auto shut-off, which is another nice feature. I\'ve read reviews from others about the coffee maker shooting water/coffee all over the place. I have not encountered this at all. Also, I\'ve used k-cups and a medium ground coffee and have had no problems with clogging or with grounds in my coffee cup. I will still keep my 12 cup coffee maker for days when at home or have company, but this single cup brew coffee maker is great when I want only want a single cup of coffee or as I head out to work. Normally I would just wait until I got to work for my first cup of coffee. With this product, I take a travel mug of coffee with me every day as I head out. No need to bother with the 12 cup coffee maker. Great product! I would definitely recommend it.'),
(5222, 7, 3, 5, '2015-11-23', 'I love this coffee maker. Since I\'m the only coffee drinker in the house it\'s perfect for me. I use ground coffee and also k cup pods. The kids love to make their hot cocoa with it. The light goes off when coffee is done brewing which is awesome cause I know with a glance. There is nothing I can say bad about this because I love everything about it.'),
(5223, 4, 1, 3, '2015-06-11', 'Great toaster, be careful when using it for the ... Great toaster, be careful when using it for the oven option it does not have an automated shut off'),
(5224, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'Five Stars Nice and easy'),
(5225, 7, 3, 3, '2016-06-03', 'This product worked well. Although when I bought it I did not know it didn\'t have a choice for your ounces. I\'m guessing you put in the amount of water you want for the amount of coffee u would like. I\'ve only used it once so I\'m not real familiar with it yet. But I think it will be ok especially for the price.'),
(5226, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-28', 'Genius ideas put to good use for a coffee lover\'s perfect coffeemaker Perfect pour, convenient, genius idea. The removable water reservoir and swinging basket for grounds are genius. I hate the mess of spilled water mixed with  coffee grounds all over my counter. The removable reservoir and swing-out style grounds basket make coffee prep so convenient and clean. The carafe is nicely weighted and gives a great pour - no dripping. The brew choices are great; I love a stronger coffee and the 1-4 cups is ideal when needed. Overall, 5 stars for all around super coffeemaker!'),
(5227, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-01', 'works great. Product as described, works great.'),
(5228, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-01', 'Love it! This coffeemaker has great features and makes excellent coffee. I especially like the removable water chamber you can fill at the sink. It\'s the second one I\'ve bought and has lasted a long time. I broke the carafe on the old one but decided to get a new one anyway. Of the many coffeemakers I\'ve owned over the years, this is by far one of the best.'),
(5229, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-30', 'Coffee Maker.......... Best coffee maker I have ever purchased!  Easy to use, easay to clean.  Brewed coffee stays HOT.'),
(5230, 6, 1, 4, '2015-02-05', 'Good features Nice compact size so it doesn\'t overwhelm the counter.  Toasts okay but tends to be uneven from side to side on the bread.  I like the extra lift available in the slots to help get small pieces out without reaching in or finding some utensil to grab it.  Very nice toaster for a good price.'),
(5231, 8, 1, 5, '2015-12-28', 'Excellent coffee maker for a college student Excellent coffee maker for a college student.  Makes me a quick cup o joe whenever I need it in the flick of a switch.  Light, quick, durable, does the job.'),
(5232, 7, 3, 4, '2016-12-09', '_ _ __  _  _ '),
(5233, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-28', 'Five Stars wise purchase great bargain'),
(5234, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-29', 'Good Gift Was a gift for a family member.  So far it is good. Nice design. Seems to be worth the price paid for it. As usual unable to find quality product in local stores. So easy to order and received in the estimated time. Very satisfied with Amazon service.'),
(5235, 2, 1, 2, '2015-05-24', 'Horrid Controls! It appears to work, but has the most confusing controls I\'ve ever seen. Every single person that tried to use it could not figure out how to shut it off. Most just gave up and pulled the plug. I finally figured out you have to turn the bottom knob most of the way to the left. Not all of the way as that turns it on permanently. A fire hazard like a toaster oven should have a clearly defined power switch...this doesn\'t and is getting returned.'),
(5236, 2, 1, 1, '2016-03-08', 'DANGEROUS ON TOAST SETTING FIREBALL IN OVEN. This over works OK as an oven but fails miserable as a toaster. Following the directions for making toast (is it really that difficult?) there is a very fine line between toasted and burnt. Using the light toast setting will get you something between lightly browned to slightly burnt with-in a very fine knob adjustment. Using the medium toast setting gives a burnt black \"toast\" I tried the dark toast setting (again following the manufacturers explicit instruction on setting the timer, temperature and function knobs and placement of the bread) just to see what would happen. By the time the timer was half done smoke was already coming out of the toaster and the \"toast\" was completely blackened, Before the timer completed the bread was completely black and smoke was coming out of the door. The \"toast\" was producing a flammable gas that was collecting and two times this gas caught fire in the oven and there was a small gas fireball, yes a FIREBALL being created in the toaster followed by a large amount of smoke being pushed out of the door. I shut it off before the timer shut the oven off. Since I purchased the \"toaster\" oven to do toast mainly with the convenience of warming other items without using the big oven, this is a giant failure. It isn\'t worth sending back so I just have to watch the toasting process and shut it off manually. In the attached photo you can see the results of the test, This is on the dark toast setting not regular oven, The bread is charred all the way through. You can see the door covered in smoke as well as smoke traces on the sides of the opening where the smoke was coming out of during the \"toasting\" process. If I could give this a negative rating I would.'),
(5237, 1, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'I absolutely love my brewer system I absolutely love my brewer system! It works very well and there are a ton of different k-cup flavors it will accept. Now that I have one, I don\'t know how I lived without one! I have a cup every morning and it\'s terrific. It\'s very user friendly and I\'d recommend it to anyone. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5238, 5, 1, 3, '2016-10-07', 'It came on time - good to make anywhere from 2 -4 cups of coffee It came on time - good to make anywhere from 2 -4 cups of coffee; more water means more coffee grounds and the filter basket cannot handle it (unless you want a very weak brew.'),
(5239, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-25', 'Good, simple oven Seems to work well - good performance for the price.'),
(5240, 8, 1, 1, '2015-12-28', 'Received this B & D 5-cup coffee make on Dec ... Received this B & D 5-cup coffee make on Dec 15, 2015. Finally bought coffee filters, tried to use it today, December 28, 2015 and it does not work. doesn\'t get hot, does not brew coffee.  I would vote no stars if that option was given.'),
(5241, 7, 3, 5, '2014-03-03', 'Why would you pay $100 or more for another name brand when this coffee maker does the same thing for half the price? It takes the k-cups or ground coffee, whichever you want.'),
(5242, 12, 1, 5, '2014-07-12', 'Great toaster and toaster oven all in one!! We gave it as a gift because our friends loved it. They are very happy with it.'),
(5243, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-22', 'This is the best little coffee maker ever (better than fancy machines!) I liked this from the moment I read the specs; the blue LED is nice, as are the tiny bottom wheels, too.  The machine is very well thought out, and functions well.  I was hesitating in buying it, b/c I thought I wanted an expresso maker that would brew 12 - 14 cups from powdery grounds ... but I wasn\'t finding any that would do that in one shot, and nothing that would even do half that, in my price range.  Reviewers were complaining about overflows and a plastic taste, which were off-putting.  Something kept pulling me back to this machine, and I\'m glad I bought it. I have no need to preset the machine the night before, so I solved the brewing question in the following manner.  First, I boiled water, and completely flushed the machine with 8 cycles of boiling water, w/a capful of vinegar each time; followed by another 4 cycles of plain boiling water.  At that point, considering the machine clean and well-flushed, I brewed the first pot of coffee. Since I wanted to see if I could stretch the output, I loaded the grounds to brew 14 cups, and then put the cool, filtered water into the reservoir in three stages (allowing the filter basket w/grounds to completely empty itself of water, before refilling the reservoir.) First, I tried three refills of 5 cups of water; then later, I tried two refills of 6 cups of water, and 1 refill of slightly over 2 cups of water.  Three refills of 5 cups makes me slightly less nervous (I\'ve spent alot of time wiping and mopping up overflows, in the past).  In between your refill stages, pour a cup and put it aside, or enjoy it on the spot.  Doing it this way, it never overflows ... and you make your grounds go further. I always use a paper filter; but my daughter brings me Starbucks coffee grinds, and the often have whole beans lurking in them.  Though the machine is well constructed, it would be very smart to get a permanent mesh filter (just to be sure you keep lurkers from blocking the brew vent), and put a paper filter inside this, so spice powders and the finely ground expresso powders don\'t gum up the works.  Then your coffee will always turn out great; and you won\'t be spending hours scrubbing stains from countertops and floors, instead of enjoying your coffee. Some reviewers had complained that the heating plate of this machine was too hot; and that the machine gave off steam and sputtered.  Well, if you see steam, you know your water is being heated up to be hot enough to brew good coffee.  When you hear sputtering, and then it stops, you can shut off the switch (which will shut the heat plate), and wait for the coffee to empty the brewing container.  Then add your next refill of water, and turn the electric back on again.  This way it brews, but doesn\'t stay on long enough to burn your coffee.  And why do you need for it to remain continuously on, when you have a microwave and can zap it hot when you want it hot?  This saves on electric, so you can afford better coffee. Nonetheless, if you happen to fall asleep for a couple of hours and find that you\'ve left your coffee on, it\'ll be in good shape when you finally do get to drink it.  This machine doesn\'t burn your coffee, as some have said.  This happened to me, and my coffee tasted wonderful!  I\'m happy!'),
(5244, 4, 1, 2, '2015-07-08', 'The door is horrible -won\'t open after only a year and a half!!!! The first year we were happy w/it.  Then the door started to be a bit difficult to open.  By now it\'s almost IMPOSSIBLE  to open!!!!  and it\'s ONLY a year and a half old!!!!  Shame on you Quisinart !'),
(5245, 6, 1, 4, '2016-12-07', 'Four Stars It does what it\'s made for.'),
(5246, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-14', 'Bought as a gift. Bought as a gift and they love it.'),
(5247, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-25', 'Five Stars Awsome...'),
(5248, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Smoothies on the go! I use this blender everyday to make my morning smoothie which is a frozen fruit and protein powder blend. It does a great job and the \"to go\" cup makes it so easy to drink on my way to work. It is a great value if you just need something small and basic.'),
(5249, 8, 1, 3, '2015-08-02', 'Burner wears out really fast I have owned both this model and a similar model by Mr. coffee. It is difficult to find a 4 cup black coffee maker with a switch. I bought the Black & Decker only because I couldn\'t find the Mr. Coffee that I liked. This model is inferior. The burner starts scratching and wearing off within a couple of weeks, despite my being very careful about not scraping the carafe against the burner. Also, it only lasted a couple of years, whereas my Mr. Coffee lasted much longer. I was finally able to find my favorite Mr. Coffee model on eBay. I will not buy another Black and Decker.'),
(5250, 10, 1, 3, '2015-01-28', 'Works for its purpose but the fluids always flow out ... Works for its purpose but the fluids always flow out of the top opening. I have to hold it down with my hand.'),
(5251, 7, 3, 5, '2015-10-15', 'My husband wanted a coffee maker to go with his coffee subscription that I bought him for our anniversary, so I bought this flexible. It is simple to use, is versatile in every sense of the word. It also uses k cups. It doesn\'t take up to much space and it works out great'),
(5252, 12, 1, 5, '2016-01-04', 'like a mini oven compared to others that i have ... this is really tiny. very tiny. like  a mini oven compared to others that i have had but it works great. i love it. i do recommend that this is for one person not a whole family. i have a family of 4 and i feel like we just abuse this too much.'),
(5253, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-09', 'A decent toaster oven. Decent toaster oven.  Not sure I could get 4 slices of toast in it at once, but that\'s not really an issue. Dislikes: It gets really hot on the outside, more so than I would have expected.  Mostly on the top and front, don\'t make the mistake of putting anything on top of this thing. The little rack slides all the way out really easily, nearly dumped a couple pieces of toast out because of it.  It would have been better if it had a little catch to prevent it from coming all the way out. Otherwise, it serves the purpose for which I bought it, making toast and re-heating leftovers.'),
(5254, 12, 1, 5, '2014-10-02', 'Five Stars We love this toaster oven. Nice to have it all in one!'),
(5255, 10, 1, 1, '2016-01-07', 'Broke after two uses. It broke after two uses.  The first smoothie was awesome and delicious.  The second smoothie really took some effort to get through.  It sounded like the blades were just spinning and spinning.  And it began to smell like it was heating up.  The third try, I used less frozen bananas (cut into small chunks) and although it mixed some of the ingredients together, it couldn\'t chop up the bananas.  The lid has also split and the plastic cup has a chip on it.  Mind you, this is only after three uses.'),
(5256, 2, 1, 1, '2016-07-11', 'Caught fire after less than a week. would give zero stars if I could. burned and smoked since the very first time i used it until one day it caught fire and I had to throw it away.'),
