(5269, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Wonderful Product It\'s the perfect personal blender, easy to clean, and does a good job - actually it does better than my mother\'s ninja blender!'),
(5270, 11, 1, 4, '2015-02-20', 'Heats up very quickly Great toaster oven; however, it gets hot really fast and burns things easily - we still have a hard time finding the \"ideal\" temperature that won\'t lead to easily and quickly burning.'),
(5271, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Did not like Keurig prices and this alternative is more than half the price.'),
(5272, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Five Stars Thank you!'),
(5273, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-09', 'Great blender. It blends food items pretty well Great blender. It blends food items pretty well. Only downside is that you have to hold the button for it to blend: if you let go, it stops blending. But, that\'s not too big of a deal, since it only takes about a minute to blend things anyway. Very much worth it, especially for the price!'),
(5274, 9, 1, 5, '2016-10-26', '... Really like this design concept Just purchased two days ago to replace the older model DC-2000 which finally started leaking from the dispenser after about 10 years of great service. Only brewed two pots, so can\'t evaluate fully, but I like the upgrades which include removable water reservoir and LED dispenser light that illuminates the cup when dispensing coffee. I\'m hoping that leaks, like those reported by a number of reviewers, can be avoided by frequent cleaning of the coffee reservoir with a Dawn Blue solution to remove coffee oils that can cause premature deterioration of the seals lining the dispenser and surrounding the hot plate. It seems a few reviewers have experienced overflow leaks from the filter basket. I can think of four factors that might cause this problem. 1. Using more than one paper filter. 2. Using a paper filter inside the permanent gold mesh filter. 3. Using too fine a grind of coffee. 4. Using too much coffee in basket. My biggest concern with this design is that the hot plate inside the coffee reservoir can cook the coffee after an hour or so which can affect coffee flavor. If you consume all the coffee in the first hour, that should not be a problem, but I would recommend pouring a hot cup of fresh water into the empty coffee reservoir or rinsing immediately with hot water to prevent burning.  This should also help with premature seal deterioration. Of course, you can set the auto off control to one hour or less to minimize flavor loss, but if the reservoir is near empty, you should still rinse immediately with hot water. I hope this review is helpful to those users experiencing leaks.  If I\'m lucky, my unit will be free from leaks for several years to come, but if not, I will update this review.'),
(5275, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-06', 'We\'re pretty picky and shopped around - we saw this model ... We\'re pretty picky and shopped around - we saw this model in stores but couldn\'t get the color we wanted.  Purchased  through Amazon for less and completely satisfied.  This should last us a good long time.'),
(5276, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-21', 'Great toaster! I am a control freak and I like this toaster.'),
(5277, 6, 1, 4, '2016-11-29', 'Toaster OK Nice toaster.  Works well.  But max setting on either side is not sufficient to toast an English Muffin on first try.  Need to push down again for 20-45 sec, depending on how light or dark you would like the toast.'),
(5278, 5, 1, 1, '2015-01-18', 'Came broken Came broken. The basket wouldn\'t stay shut. Hopefully I will be able to return it for one that works...'),
(5279, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-04', 'Great oven! Great gift and the toaster is the best!'),
(5280, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-22', 'Black+Decker exceeds expectations with this one I recently moved into a place with a tiny kitchen and no oven. I agonized over what toaster oven to get, as I needed something that didn\'t take up too much counter space and I could use as a real oven in a pinch. After browsing through a few brick and mortar stores, I decided on Black and Decker because the heating elements just seem a lot bigger and higher quality than the other brands. I wanted a convection option and a big enough oven for a frozen pizza. This toaster oven hit all the required marks and knocked it out of the park. I am very happy with this purchase. It takes a big longer than a regular toaster to make toast, but that doesn\'t bother me. The oven setting heats up fast and seems to hold temperature fairly well. You can\'t expect a sub$100 toaster oven to behave like a regular oven and yet this one is pretty awesome.'),
(5281, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-12', 'Five Stars Works great.'),
(5282, 5, 1, 4, '2015-11-01', 'Not perfect, but good enough! This maker works well, makes good coffee, and offers a few useful choices for the brew, without being too complex. When it was new, we had trouble with the water reservoir not setting completely down in it\'s slot, with the result that sometimes not all of the water made it into the machine. In other words, the valve was a little fussy. After a few uses, and tamping the container down before each use, it\'s ceased to be a problem. So, we\'re happy. There doesn\'t seem to be a perfect coffee maker, but this one is good enough.'),
(5283, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-15', 'Great Toaster Oven Works great'),
(5284, 12, 1, 5, '2014-10-26', 'wesome appliance for the money love this guy, we buy a new one every year'),
(5285, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-25', 'Five Stars Best coffee pot, easy to clean and use'),
(5286, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-30', 'Great toast every time. I\'m so pleased with this toaster! It\'s the perfect size and it does a great job. I would buy it again!.'),
(5287, 8, 1, 1, '2016-08-24', 'Old school coffee maker. There are things that - I thought coffee makers automatically had because we\'re not In the 1980\'s. This coffee machine does not have a stop drip if you remove the carafe. It does not have an automatic turnoff - will stay on all night. Im not even sure how it\'s UL listed.'),
(5288, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-05', 'FIRE HAZARD, DO NOT BUY When I first started using this toaster oven, it was great. But here I am 8 months later and it almost burned my apartment down. The top coil now heats to maximum heat thereby burning everything, and the coil won\'t turn off when the knobs are in the off position, so the only way to turn the coil off was to unplug the machine. Thank god I didn\'t make toast for breakfast and then run off to work, or the coil would have been on all day. DO NOT BUY THIS TOASTER OVEN. I contacted Cuisinart, and they told me it was a \"warranty issue\" and that I would have to pay to ship it to them and then pay them to ship a new one to me. Jerks. I wonder if they\'d like paying for a lawsuit when my apartment burns down?'),
(5289, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-13', 'Great coffee pot for the price Great coffee pot for the price.  I usually buy Cuisinart but had electrical issues with the last one so decided to try a cheaper coffee pot.  I like the pull out water reservoir and the pull out filter area, makes it much easier to use.  The first few uses did taste a little plasticy even after running it with water a couple of times first, but this went away.'),
(5290, 11, 1, 5, '2014-01-16', 'Great! I bought the toaster for my sister for Christmas and she loves it. The package came in the time I was told it would be here.'),
