(5301, 6, 1, 4, '2015-06-17', 'Four Stars Very good. Cannot get 5 stars for it burns a bit my waffles in the right compartment only.'),
(5302, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-28', 'Pretty nice so far! So far so good; nice features, easy to operate, program and liking the filling option (you can pour into the reservoir or remove reservoir and fill at water source).  Also doesn\'t seem to dribble out of the carafe as much as many of the others out in the market.  The only issue I have had was my own fault; I haven\'t been consistent with the filling choice so on a couple of occasions I filled the reservoir tank but forgot to empty the carafe!  A couple of messes later I think I\'m starting to learn!  Totally my fault on that...  I hope it lasts a good long while as I do like it quite a lot so far.'),
(5303, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-24', 'Great size and price The good outweighs the bad so I gave it 4 stars but there\'s one thing I\'d like to suggest that the manufacture consider when doing their next redesign.  I purchased this toaster oven just to toast things, not for baking small meals like it is also able to do.  The circular dial you need to turn for toasting bread, gives you several pictures to indicate the level of darkness you want for your bread.  The problem for me is that out of the 360 degrees you can turn on the dial, you have to be able to stop somewhere between the 10 and 30 degree mark for toast.  The dial has decent resistance and I have a hard time getting it exactly right. I\'ve burned a lot of toast getting used to it and always feel that I have to keep an eye on it because my dial may be off by a few degrees.  That said, what I really like about it is its size.  Very small and compact for the my kitchen counter but it doesn\'t look cheap.  I was looking at ovens up to $200 but couldn\'t find one as compact as this, which was a big selling point for me.  The price was absolutely awesome and for that I think I can wrestle a bit with the dial every morning.  Another thing I really like is the quality of toasting it gives our bread each morning. When I get the right place on the dial, it\'s perfectly toasted.  Make sure you remove the baking pan from underneath the grates (yes I missed that one on my first try) or your toast will be moist and un-toasted on one side and stick to the grates.  I also ran it empty a couple of times just to burn off any possible manufacturing fumes.'),
(5304, 12, 1, 1, '2016-03-14', 'Cheap and broken on delivery Top toaster didn\'t work from first try. Lever inoperable and had to return.  Frustrating!'),
(5305, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-02', 'Five Stars Great toaster.'),
(5306, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-01', 'Makes great garlic bread! Controls are a little wonky, but it does the job. Still haven\'t found the exact right setting for toast the way I like it, seems to toast kind of uneven. Made some great garlic bread in it the other day though! even my husband noticed something different about how it tasted in there vs. the oven. Nice to have for heating up pizza & other things, especially on hot days when I have no desire to turn on the oven!'),
(5307, 4, 1, 5, '2015-07-24', 'Great size and does not throw off a lot of ... I use this over every day for something. Great size and does not throw off a lot of heat.'),
(5308, 5, 1, 2, '2015-08-23', 'Really liked this coffee maker until it stopped working after 1 ... Really liked this coffee maker until it stopped working after 1 year of use. It\'s a good price but cheap.'),
(5309, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-30', 'One of the better coffee makers we\'ve owned One of the better coffee makers we\'ve owned.  The removable cup base is handy for taller mugs.  Would buy again.'),
(5310, 10, 1, 3, '2015-04-17', 'Doesn\'t blend smoothly You will have chunks with this blender no matter how long you run it.'),
(5311, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Perfect I just want coffee.... I don\'t need bells and whistles, just coffee.  This machine is perfect and just the right size for one or two people on a lazy morning.  It brews a perfect pot every time.'),
(5312, 12, 1, 3, '2016-11-28', 'Cancel button was much needed upgrade from original, which ... Cancel button was much needed upgrade from original, which I owned and lasted 5 years. Quality looks same as previous one, which ended up with a stuck temperature control and almost burnt the unit from overheating. I suspect this unit has same flaw. After reading reviews, I did run the unit for 2 30-min cycles. First cycle produced fumes, probably some packing material left inside the control compartment. Second cycle did continue to give off plastic odor that dissipated over subsequent uses.'),
(5313, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-08', 'Small but mighty Great little coffee maker. Perfect for 1'),
(5314, 6, 1, 4, '2014-07-21', 'This replaces one I bought in 2006. Maybe the ... This replaces one I bought in 2006.  Maybe the first one should have lasted longer than it did, but while it was working it was very effective and the appliance itself is attractive on the counter.  I hope this one lasts a bit longer.'),
(5315, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Love it! I love this new brewer so much! I personally only drink one cup of coffee a day, and I originally had the Keurig B40, but my husband was always complaining, because he is the kind of guy that drinks a lot of coffee a day, and he hated having to keep making one cup at a time! So when we found out that there was a new Keurig that would brew a carafe, we got really excited! We love it. It\'s easy to use and it looks really fancy, too! And a perk, we received it for free to test and review! Awesome!'),
(5316, 1, 1, 4, '2016-07-01', 'People need to calm down and get a hobby. What is everyone freaking out about? All of this bluster about the machine only taking Keurig-brand cups... ...yeah, AND? When hasn\'t it? Here\'s the thing: just like EVERY OTHER KEURIG, there are reusable cups in which people can put their own coffee grounds. Even Keurig makes one! Honestly, people need to go volunteer somewhere or get a hobby or do something other than gripe about things that aren\'t true. I did not buy mine from Amazon, but I am an active Prime member and I think I\'m a reliable source. :) I really like the Keurig 2.0. I love that it has a high altitude setting (I live in CO), and a \"strong\" setting. I also bought the Contigo/Keurig travel mug which fits perfectly under the dispenser if you take off the drip tray - it\'s a great mug! Anyway, I gave it four stars because I\'ve only had it for a few weeks and don\'t know how durable it will be, but for right now, it\'s pretty awesome!'),
(5317, 9, 1, 1, '2016-04-23', 'Don\'t do it. Well, it lasted about four weeks. Then the seal on the reservoir busted  it\'s a narrow access internal spring. So now when it brews it leaks heavily. If I\'m brewing anymore than two cups I have to do a fast swap to another cup to catch the overflow. Spoke with customer service. They\'ll replace one coffeemaker if you ship it to them. But that\'ll cost another $25 and I\'m wondering if I should add to my losses if I only get another coffeemaker that\'ll break.'),
(5318, 5, 1, 4, '2015-01-10', 'Good Coffee Maker The product is very sturdy and value for money. The machine is easy to use and fits in well into my kitchen.'),
(5319, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-22', 'I have had it on my counter for 3 weeks now and have used it several times and love it. Yes I purchased this Convection oven as a Christmas present to myself.  I have had it on my counter for 3 weeks now and have used it several times and love it.  Yes, the outside does get hot, but what do you expect?  It\'s metal and it\'s going to get hot (no brainer to me)  I have not tried the Convection feature yet but planning on it soon.'),
(5320, 7, 3, 1, '2015-01-02', 'I don\'t not recommend this product at all. The water barely gets hot. It takes a lot longer to brew then my other keruig. And even when my tea cup is full and I turn it off the water keeps pouring out. I hate this product.'),
(5321, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-03', 'Magic Box Turns Gooey Dough Into Bread And Other Neat Stuff This is what I cook with half the time. It\'s amazing. I put cold raw stuff in it, turn that timer knob and it makes like a clicking sound for every notch I turn it past, then the red light is on and the burner lights up, and it makes a clicking sound for all those notches it passes back through on its way back to zero, then it dings and I go get my stuff and it\'s cooked! I can eat it now! Which is good, because I was hungry the whole time, that\'s why I put food in there in the first place.'),
(5322, 4, 1, 4, '2015-05-30', 'Great toaster oven for price, watch for gaps... Bought this in March 2014. We literally use it AT LEAST once a day. Seriously one of the best purchases we have made, we\'re definitely getting out money\'s worth. Cooking needs from baking, toasting, reheating, defrosting, etc etc. The pan gets dirty fast and stuff sticks to it pretty bad so we always have aluminium foil covering it. The middle of the rack is a lot flimsier than expected. Always afraid I am going to break it when doing a \'heavy\' clean, but so far it has held up. Only real complaint: On the top right corner where the door opens/closes, steam \'escapes\'. It is only that side. I can push the door with my hand and the steam stops escaping, but only if I keep my hand pressed on the door. Looks like it does not \'seal\' properly, but it hasn\'t been a huge burden, more of an annoyance really. I actually noticed it the day I first used it...but I kept forgetting to return it so now I am stuck with it. I\'m not saying I regret the purchase, because we don\'t, but I wish I had been more proactive and seen if I have a semi-defective product and could have repurchased for a toaster oven with a \'better seal\'.'),
(5323, 11, 1, 4, '2014-10-18', 'easy to use Gets the job done, easy to use.'),
(5324, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-15', 'My husband and I really like the convenience of the FlexBrew. We each get whatever type of coffee we want, it is ready quickly right into our cups or to-go mugs. We like the ease of just pouring the amount of water we choose, and whether we want ground coffee or K Cups. Even just hot water for tea. Cleaning is easy and hassle free, also. The only negative thing is that it is noisy but after a while you just don\'t notice it. We have recommended this Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffeemakers to several of our friends.'),
(5325, 9, 1, 5, '2015-07-14', 'Five Stars the best coffee pot I ever bought'),
(5326, 11, 1, 1, '2014-03-05', 'Disappointed I travel a lot so though I ordered this a couple months ago, I didn\'t actually get to open it until a couple months after it arrived and it arrived broken :( The warranty expired 1 week after. My fault I know, but there was also no instruction manual which made me think it was a previously returned item that was just reshipped.'),
(5327, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-31', 'Works great.... Excellent transaction....everything as promised....works great....'),
(5328, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-15', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(5329, 6, 1, 1, '2014-06-01', 'Didn\'t last more than a month I bought this toaster for my father as a gift. In less than a month, one side/slot didn\'t toast. I was very very disappointed.  Since I had already thrown away the box, I didn\'t bother with trying to return it and he simply dealt with the inconvenience of toasting two slices of bread one at a time.'),
(5330, 8, 1, 1, '2014-08-15', 'Not recommended. When brewing it leaks on the side Not recommended.  When brewing it leaks on the side.  I bought this because It\'s cheap,  but because there is no pause when you get coffee from the container while brewing,  even if you turn it off it keeps on dripping.'),
(5331, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-11', 'One Star I would never buy this again.'),
(5332, 8, 1, 5, '2015-01-14', 'Good basic coffeemaker I bought this coffee maker for my 85 year old dad for Christmas. He loves it and uses it everyday. It is basic with no extra features, which is just what he wanted. He likes to color (black) and the fact that it makes a full 5 cups of coffee.'),
(5333, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-18', 'Four Stars Works great!'),
(5334, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-10', 'workhorse At $64.00 this is a workhorse...frozen pizza goes in at 3am..frozen waffels go in at 7am....bagels with cheese go in at lunch time....bacon gets cooked at midnight....no burned food, even cooking and its a brand I know...B&D'),
(5335, 7, 3, 5, '2016-09-22', 'Very happy I chose this one it\'s perfect,for me.most important the coffee is great'),
(5336, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Five Stars This was a gift for my friend. She likes it very much.'),
(5337, 4, 1, 1, '2015-01-19', 'One Star Stopped working after one year.'),
(5338, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-24', 'I HAVE HAD THESE COFFEE MAKERS WHEN THEY FIRST CAME OUT OTHER MODELS WERE A LITTLE MORE EXPENSIVE !! HOWEVER !!!!! THEY WORKED THIS IS THE BIGGEST PIECE OF JUNK I HAVE EVER HAD THE FIRST COUPLE OF DAYS IT WAS OK AFTER THAT THE MADE MORE NOISE THAN MY RACE CAR MORE WATER ON COUNTER THAN IN THE CUP SO I CLEANED IT STILL PROBLEMS ONE RIGHT AFTER ANOTHER I WILL NEVER BY OFF BRAND AGAIN AND FOR SURE NOTHING FROM THIS COMPANY I USE MY COFFEE MAKER AT LEAST 6 TO 7 TIMES A DAY I WOULD NOT EVEN WASTE MY TIME RETURNING RIGHT IN THE TRASH AFTER 1 MONTH I WOULD NOT WANT MY ENEMY TO USE IT NEVER MIND MY FRIENDS'),
(5339, 4, 1, 3, '2016-06-06', 'The name doesn\'t always mean quality. The door keeps getting stuck when opening and closing.'),
(5340, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-21', 'Attractive and functional I\'m very pleased with this toaster. It is easy to see the toasting options and dial, toasts well, and looks very attractive on my counter. The cord very easily fits to go out the back of the toaster, so it doesn\'t show on the counter. I read that was a concern in some reviews, but it\'s really not an issue. The way mine is arranged, I only see the cord where it plugs into the wall, not on the counter. I\'ve found the toasting to be reliable and satisfactory.'),
(5341, 7, 3, 5, '2014-05-30', 'After trying other single-serve coffeemakers without success, my expectations were about as low as the price for this unit. Was I surprised !!!! Hamilton Beach has this figured out and at an awesome price. Just as advertised, takes 3-4 minutes, coffee is hot, small profile and is dependable. I never knew when the other 2 would foul up - the time I spent babying them. At this price it will make an awesome gift for someone who wants to try the single serve either with their own coffee or the pods.'),
(5342, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-02', 'good product Good little toaster oven.'),
(5343, 3, 1, 5, '2014-03-19', 'Best Oven we\'ve had yet Very happy with this unit and it\'s ease of use. Easy to clean and works very well. Toasts the bagels just right!'),
(5344, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-02', 'Five Stars Compact, works well'),
(5345, 9, 1, 3, '2016-06-04', 'Three Stars This coffee pot  leaks.'),
(5346, 4, 1, 4, '2016-12-14', 'A good toaster oven that is still working well after almost 3 years. This is a good toaster oven. I would call it medium or small-medium size and it\'s just right for my needs. I mainly use it for bagels, toast, rolls and sometimes little pizzas. It has worked well and I have had it for almost 3 years without any problems. I would recommend this toaster oven.'),
(5347, 11, 1, 2, '2014-06-13', 'Safety Hazard Ok, I was in the need for a new toaster-oven since the \"$6-Special\" I picked up at a 2nd hand store a dozen years ago finally died.  Admittedly, I did not do my research before purchasing this unit at a local retailer. Pros: 1) Size, 2) Appearance, 3) Price (<$30) 4) Actually makes pretty decent toast Cons: 1) Temperature - This appliance does not get anywhere near as warm as the settings would indicate - I set the dial for 400 to reheat some pizza and the BEST the unit would do was 330 on the BAKE setting. 2) The Worst thing about this oven is that it does NOT have any type of detent or stop to keep the shelf rack from sliding all the way out with the slightest pull.  This is a huge safety issue in my book that outweighs all of the Pros combined.  I will be donating this item to a local fundraiser and purchasing something else.'),
(5348, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-14', 'I love this toaster I love this toaster.  It takes up less space than my older, more expensive toaster and cooks more evenly. Very happy with this purchase');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(5349, 1, 1, 1, '2016-05-21', 'Not as good as i thought I thought this was going to be a really neat coffee maker because it said there were many cup sizes and it looked like it had a bigger water reservoir from my original Keurig. I was not happy when we received it because after two regular size cups of coffee the water was almost out it should hold more then it does. Also not happy about how it is suppose to have 9 different cup sizes when all I ever saw was 6oz., 8oz. or 10oz. Only three options on the screen. What happened to the other 6 sizes I will never know. Then I decided to buy cappuccino k cups only to find they do not work on this. After only having this for a month and using it for about 5 times total it has decided to stop working properly. The seller was very hard to get to respond until I had Amazon step in and they contacted them for me. I was given a refund and will be sending this back. Biggest mistake buying it in the first place.'),
(5350, 7, 3, 1, '2015-12-28', 'The brewer worked okay for the first several brews, then would not work properly afterwards. The unit would either flash incorrectly that there was no water or would not dispense hot water. I am returning the product and will not purchase again.'),
(5351, 4, 1, 4, '2015-07-17', 'Great Little Totaster Oven - CANNOT BUY REPLACEMENT ELEMENTS! This is a great little oven. Easy to clean, cooks well.  Its the second one I bought. The first one only lasted about 3 year then one of the elements cracked and eventually burned out.  YOU CANNOT SIMPLY BUY A REPLACEMENT ELEMENT! It cannot be repaired, so it ends up in a landfill forever and ever.  I searched for other comparable ovens but non of them had replacement elements either - unless of course I wanted to spend hundredreds and hundreds of dollars!  Anyway, I love the product except don\'t expect it to last for years and years and years. Hope this helps.'),
(5352, 10, 1, 4, '2015-05-20', 'Maybe upgrade the motor?? This is a replacement for one I have used for several years.  There is a smell when running the motor and it seems to get heated up.  I never had this with my last one.'),
(5353, 3, 1, 4, '2016-01-20', 'OUTSTANDING! I love this thing!  The only downside is that the top gets extremely hot.  I should expect that I guess, but was not expecting it.  Other than that, this oven is OUTSTANDING!!!'),
(5354, 12, 1, 4, '2016-10-05', 'Works well as toaster and I can see where it ... Works well as toaster and I can see where it would work as a toaster oven as I cooked off all the manufacturing chemicals and such before I put food in it. I see they make a four slice version which has a bigger toaster over component and would have purchased that had I known about it.'),
(5355, 9, 1, 3, '2016-09-03', 'Great idea. Great idea.. Just lacked the thought that unless your only using a standard size coffee cup. A lot of travel mugs don\'t fit underneath it. You have to pour into a smaller size cup then pour that cup into your mug. Plus you don\'t get the aroma of the coffee brewing.. The gauge doesn\'t work properly either. I brewed 8 cups and gauge said full. When another time I did a full 12 cups and said the same very thing.. Great for use if your only using 12-14oz cups at home..'),
(5356, 12, 1, 4, '2016-03-26', 'Ingenious... How ingenious for a small galley kitchen; I threw away appliances taking up three times the counter space. Needs a wire grill to fit in the pan.'),
(5357, 11, 1, 4, '2015-01-07', 'Good toaster oven Good toaster oven. Be advised, the top does get hot when it\'s on. I kept cork coasters (which are meant to be used for placing hot pots and pans on so as not to damage a counter or a table) on top of it until they almost caught fire. So, not just warm, it gets very hot. Other than that small gripe, it does a great job of toasting bread, broiling some fish, making cheese sandwiches. Removable tray makes crumb clean-up easy. I haven\'t checked the accuracy of the temperature setting on the dial.'),
(5358, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-30', 'Five Stars This blender is absolutely perfect for making a smoothie.  Easy to operate, easy to clean, I love this thing.'),
(5359, 6, 1, 4, '2016-07-08', 'Seems to be a good toaster at a reasonable cost and it works It isn\'t a very expensive toaster, but man, I went through quite a few trying to find a good one. So far I get my toast evenly done. This toaster is lightweight (I keep it in a cabinet, so I am pleased it is easy to pick up and put away, etc.). It is rather cheap feeling...which is fine (I keep it in a cabinet...right?). I like the warm feature which works perfectly. I\'ll keep you posted.'),
(5360, 6, 1, 4, '2015-05-15', 'Be careful not to turn dial up too high! I saw great reviews for this on Amazon. So when our old one gave up the ghost, we bought this one.  I\'ve had a few issues with it so far though. . . When toasting a plain piece of bread for the first time, I set it on medium (dial straight up) and just pushed the handle down.  The toast came out blackened on both sides when it eventually finished. The second try, I backed off the dial to the number 3 and after pushing the lever down, also hit the bagel button.  The toast didn\'t come out as black this time.  More of a mixture of black and toasty brown. The third try, I selected 2 with the bagel button.  This time the toast came out browned (few small black areas) on one side.  And, perfectly brown on the other side.  For whatever reason, it didn\'t toast both sides constantly? We tried a bagel with the dial at 2 and the babel button on.  Perfectly browned! So, not sure what the higher settings on the dial are for?  Don\'t want to go there . . . Also, I like the lift feature to get the bread out of the cooking basket.'),
(5361, 9, 1, 3, '2015-02-27', 'Makes great hot coffee but cord way too short Makes great hot coffee but cord way too short. Must be a joke. We have to unplug it every morning in order to rinse and fill. If you have top cabinets there is no way to open lid in order to fill, empty or replace grinds. Have to reset clock daily will probably return.'),
(5362, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', 'Easy to Use and Works Great Bought this toaster oven as an upgrade for the office kitchen. I chose it because it\'s the newest version of the last one we had which everyone in the office loved. It\'s a good size, easy to use, and cooks evenly. Satisfied with this product once again!.'),
(5363, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'Five Stars Great for small smoothies. Don\'t overdue it with large chunks or dry ingredients. Crushed ice only.'),
(5364, 10, 1, 2, '2015-09-24', '2 Stars for not selling separate cups. It\'s a good, cheap blender. I find it frustrating that they do not sell the blender cups separately. That used to be one of the primary benefits for buying one of these blenders.'),
(5365, 11, 1, 2, '2014-08-03', 'Tiny Very small. I live in a small monthly with no oven. I had to shop for special pans that fit in it. The temp settings are off. At 450 deg, it does not even brown. On the flip side, it is good for small pizzas if you set it on Toast and 15 minutes.'),
(5366, 3, 1, 1, '2014-12-11', 'I did a super clean of my old toaster oven and use it too big to be considered a toaster oven. it takes longer to make toast and quick items because it\'s too big. I did a super clean of my old toaster oven and use it. I\'ll find someone who needs a mini oven. I would have returned it, but felt I had to experiment with this oven because I heard it was the \"best\" The next \"toaster\" oven I purchase will be based on counter space size, and heat element power.'),
(5367, 8, 1, 4, '2016-08-26', 'Great value coffeemaker I was happy to try out the smaller version of the Black & Decker that I already had. The coffeemaker has a very small footprint and can fit on a bookshelf. It brews coffee in about 5 minutes, and it tastes great. There is no auto shut-off, just the switch to start brewing process. It brews just enough for myself and my wife each morning. Great value.'),
(5368, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'This coffee machine is simple practical and very reliable! ... This coffee machine is simple practical and very reliable! It is very practical when you have to do a quick coffee in the morning. I actually have no complaints about it! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review'),
(5369, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Works great. Found out later that H Works great. Found out later that H.B. also makes a four slice. Wish that I had known this I would have bought it instead of the two slice. The four slice didn\'t show up on the Amazon sight.'),
(5370, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-28', 'Four Stars Good Product.'),
(5371, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-05', 'i cannot say anything bad about this piece this is my second one.  i cannot say anything bad about this piece.  toast, toaster oven... bam...it\'s fantastic.'),
(5372, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-05', 'Five Stars It does its job properly.'),
(5373, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-10', 'wow! This is amazing! Is personal and it\'s really good quality I was so excited when it came in and it came in fast too! It\'s awesome! I make milkshakes and smoothies all the time now.'),
(5374, 7, 3, 3, '2015-12-02', 'I bought this coffee maker because I liked the idea of being able to use coffee grounds or K-cups, but now I only use it for coffee grounds. This coffee maker works great for ground coffee, but when I use K-cups, the coffee comes out very weak. A bit disappointed to say the least.'),
(5375, 1, 1, 2, '2016-10-02', 'Slow preheating and requires constant addition of water This is the slowest Keurig I have ever used. It takes several minutes to preheat the water before each and every cup is brewed. I dont know if its because of the frequent and lengthy pre-heating time or what, but there is always a ton of condensation inside the water well. Because this unit has a clear, not a gray water well, you can see every droplet clinging to the inside. This in no way affects function of course, but it looks gross. You have to add water very frequently, because it will not brew if even remotely low (like halfway full). The unit is quite tall, so I also had to purchase a coffee cab to go under so I can slide it out from under the cabinet to change the pod every time. Since the is unit is top heavy, it wobbles when opening the top. Although the brewing works fine, I am not pleased with this unit overall for the above reasons.'),
(5376, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-31', 'I had another identical B&D unit for many years until ... I had another identical B&D unit for many years until a huge storm electrical surge took most of most appliances in the Kitchen. We decided to buy an identical new one because of the previous experienced reliability and easiness of operate. Yes, it gets hot on the top if operated for more than 10 minutes so keep it away from little children\'s hands, but that is true with most toasters.'),
(5377, 5, 1, 5, '2014-04-22', 'Very Good Coffee Maker I purchased the Hamilton Beach 46201 coffee maker because it has a detachable water reservoir, which I wanted so as to be able to clean it out. Other coffee makers without a detachable water reservoir are hard to clean as often as necessary here in the South where mold develops easily, especially in moist environments. Also, the Hamilton Beach 46201 coffee maker has some pretty nice selectable features, such as plate temperature and brew strength. All in all, it is a very good coffee maker, probably the best that I have owned, and I have owned several. The only drawback that I can find is that about a tablespoon of coffee remains in the decanter, held in there by the plastic rim. Other than that, the Hamilton Beach 46201 coffee maker is excellent in my opinion.'),
(5378, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-18', 'Simple and sleek Between my home, my office, and family homes, I\'ve tried all the different lines of Keurig machines and this one is my favorite. If you are the only coffee drinker in your home or you really just have one cup a day, this one is perfect. It\'s compact and fits under my counter nicely, looks sleek and not at all bulky, and brews one fresh cup perfectly. The bigger machines are nice too, if you have the need for a larger water reservoir, but if you\'re looking for basic and simple, this really is the best machine. I do, however, recommend getting a reusable filter and your own coffee rather than using the K-cups. Those get very expensive and are pretty wasteful. This machine works perfectly with my reusable filter.'),
(5379, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-16', 'Four Stars Very happy with it.'),
(5380, 2, 1, 1, '2016-08-21', 'Made by al-quaida? I was going to buy one. I am not buying one now because while i was reading the reviews it made my phone combust. Thanks China.'),
(5381, 11, 1, 1, '2014-05-28', 'stopped working after 20 uses I changed my review from 4 stars to 1 star because now it totally stopped working, only after less than 20 uses. Since I don\'t use it very often, it already passed the return time window of Amazon. So have to contact the manufacturer to return or replace.'),
(5382, 4, 1, 2, '2016-02-03', 'Two Stars Lower Heating rod died in 6 months.'),
(5383, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-19', 'Easy  AM Coffee Nice Pot Simple And Easy To Use'),
(5384, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-28', 'A Perfect Coffee Maker There is nothing about this coffee maker that I don\'t love! The taste, the wheels, the heat feature, being able to fill it from the sink, the coffee basket at the touch of a button, the look with my stainless appliances. A perfect coffee maker!'),
(5385, 3, 1, 4, '2015-10-20', 'Performs well. I purchased this Black & Decker countertop oven to replace my full-sized oven that had become non-functional. Though I have had to make a few adjustments in my cooking habits, this little oven has kept up surprisingly well. I have used it to broil steaks, bake cookies and muffins, toast bagels and bread, roast vegetables, and will be baking a cake in it later tonight. Everything I have made so far has turned out very nicely -- I wouldn\'t guess that any of the food had been made in anything but a regular oven. There are few downsides to this oven. I do wish the digital display was backlit -- I use a wheelchair and have to be directly in front of the unit to be able to read the display, and I feel that a backlight would help readability from different angles. Also note that it is well worth buying a second rack, since the unit only comes with one. Lastly, I\'d love it if the oven could handle a 16\" pizza stone, but that\'s just me being picky. Overall, this is a great little oven. I actually prefer it over my mother\'s rotisserie convection oven, which was twice as expensive and takes up more counter space without the benefit of a larger cooking interior.'),
(5386, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-21', 'Think twice. Disappointed.  Uneven toasting from the very beginning.  One year old -- only 2 slices working on 4 slice toaster.  Not worth the cost.'),
(5387, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-30', 'AWESOME PRODUCT HIGHLY RECOMMENDED I cannot say enough nice things about this product.  It is simply fantastic.  It can be a little complicated to use but it works really great.  It gets super hot up to I think 400 or 450 degrees.  While preheating it shows the temperature.  It bakes great.  It is fantastic baking Pizza.  Our previous brand did not bake pizza very well.  Never expected a B&D unit to be this good.  I must have purchased it based on reviews of some sort.  Well worth the price.'),
(5388, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-24', 'Awesome Keurig product This is our 2nd Keurig brewer. Our 1st one lasted 7 years. I hope we get that longevity from this one.  The power button is difficult to actuate with man fingers but Keurig is great.'),
(5389, 11, 1, 4, '2014-06-24', 'Fantastic price - Decent Toaster It\'s a toaster oven with no bells and whistles, but for the price, you can\'t beat it. My only complaint is that the temperature controls take some getting used to - this toaster heats up QUICKLY so it takes a bit of time to learn how to use it without creating charcoal out of toast.'),
(5390, 5, 1, 4, '2014-03-10', 'Pretty good coffee maker The controls are just a little too complicated.  It took me a while to figure them out.  By now, I can do it in the dark when I\'m still half-asleep!  The very first time that I ran it I used just water, which is a good thing because the water came spilling out over the side.  I\'d read in some other reviews about this so I was partially expecting it.  The lesson is to make sure the carafe is really in the correct position.  I think what happens is that if the carafe is not opening the check-valve at the bottom of the filter basket, it will fill up and overflow the sides of the filter basket and then run down and make a mess.  In my case, it was just water and I caught it quickly.  Never had that problem since.  I like the choice of temperature of the hot plate.  I also like the removeable water container in the back.  It\'s a lot more convenient that trying to pour water from a carafe into the top the way I had to do it with my previous coffee maker.  The swing-out filter basket holder is easier to deal with than the slide-in type of other coffee-makers too.  Overall I\'m pretty happy with it.'),
(5391, 1, 1, 1, '2016-09-17', 'Regular size stainless steel travel cups DO NOT FIT I am very sorry that Keurig has not decided to make any of their coffee pots compatible to standard size travel cups.  I got excited about the description on this one and decided to give it a shot.  Nope, even with taking out the bottom screen it did not fit my travel cup.  And as I doubt that Keurig\'s coffee is that much better than any other brand\'s coffee maker as far as making a good tasting cup of coffee,  I am not going to spend my precious time in the morning brewing two cups or a carafe and then pouring them into my travel cup.  For as much as you pay for one of these, they ought to at least make them so your travel cup fits!!.'),
(5392, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-17', 'Five Stars Excellent for price.'),
(5393, 5, 1, 4, '2016-12-15', 'Nice, except faceplate fell off within 24 hrs Only had this for 2 days.  I like the features, PRICE!, and everything works well except for the faceplate coming off the second day in use.  Others have mentioned this and it is clearly a design flaw.  I was extremely careful removing it from the box so that didn\'t break the plate. In assembly a screw penetrates two plastic parts of the faceplate.  That is supposed to keep the plate in place.  But in assembly those screws are cracking the plastic parts.  I\'ve used tape to secure things for now.  If the coffee maker continues to perform well, I\'ll epoxy the tabs to the body for a more permanent solution.  Should be easy.  I got the Maker for $20 via an Alexa Prime promotion.  So I can\'t complain.  Won\'t return it b/c I would probably get another machine whose face plate will be defective too. It\'s crazy Hamilton Beach has not taken this feedback and revised the assembly protocol.  I\'ve attached a pic of my temporary repair.  Like I say, for the price I can live with it...especially since a repair is easy. BTW, here is the link to the Alexa Prime promotion site.  Worth checking out.  I think the coffee maker is still $20 if you use your Echo, Echo Dot, or Echo Tap to place the order. I also think you must be a Prime subscriber. https://www.amazon.com/b?node=14552177011&ref_=pe_1840220_218138410_echo_crm_alexadeals_12_09.'),
(5394, 7, 3, 4, '2016-05-07', 'So far the Coffee Maker seems to work well. I purchased for my aunt as a gift.'),
(5395, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-08', 'Excellent. compact and as advertised. Excellent.'),
(5396, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-21', 'It works great! We have had no problems with this toaster oven. It is compact, so it does not take up a lot of counter space. It is easy to use, and is functional. Toast always comes out a little dry though, so it does not get used much for that. We use it mainly for small batch cooking and reheating. It is so much nicer not to heat up the oven and house when we just want to make, say, a few chicken nuggets, or re-crisp leftovers. Because it isn\'t preheated like a standard oven, I\'ve had to adjust baking times. That is not a big deal at all to me. It is also nice to be able to choose from the wire rack or the solid tray, depending on what I\'m cooking. We are pleased with this purchase.'),
(5397, 7, 3, 5, '2014-01-10', 'I have had this machine for three weeks and it hasnu2019t messed up one time. I read all the reviews because I got this as a Christmas gift and was contemplating returning it and using the credit toward a Keurig. The box says that it expresses more coffee from the K-cup than the leading brand (Keurig, Iu2019m assuming), by the way. Well, I decided to try it out first and if it started acting up as described in several reviews (water everywhere, sputteringu2026) I would return it. After using it for three weeks and following the very simple DIRECTIONS that came with the coffeemaker, I have decided that human error is whatu2019s causing the problems u2013 not the machine. Do the following for a great cup of coffee each time and no messes: 1 u2013 Use the fill-indicator where you put the water into to determine just how much water you really have in there. For a stronger cup, only fill to the 8oz. notification; for a slightly weaker cup, fill to the 10 oz. notification. 2 u2013 Use a WIDE-rimmed coffee mug. I would say that a cup that is AT LEAST 4u201d across the rim is what you should be using. The water gets hot very quickly and pours out in a strong stream (which is why I think this coffeemaker is advertised as expressing more coffee from the K-cup than the leading competitor) which tells me that the pressure buildup from heating so quickly COUPLED WITH a coffee mug that is of standard-rim width instead of a WIDE-rimmed width is the reason so many people are complaining of splatter. 3 u2013 Be sure to PUSH the K-cup you use (I use Green Mountain brand) ALL THE WAY DOWN into the K-cup reservoir. Look for two things: You want the rim of the K-cup and the rim of the K-cup holder/reservoir to be level with each other! AND u2013 you want to make sure that the little foil u201cbubbleu201d or mound that every unopened/punctured K-cup has gets suctioned into the K-cup u2013 itu2019s a vacuum effect from the K-cup being punctured underneath. 4 u2013 You must REMEMBER to push down the little bar in the very front of the machine that is attached to the K-cup reservoir. I forgot to do this once and all I got in my cup was hot water. You must push down this bar in order to CONNECT the K-cup you are using WITH the water! 4 - Every time you make a cup of coffee and take out the K-Cup reservoir to dump out the used K-cup, there is that bottom latch to take care of. It is the round, swinging part that the coffee goes through just before it drips into the cup. Make sure to firmly click it back onto the bottom of the K-cup reservoir. 5 u2013 Lastly, be sure to keep the sharp, metal puncture blade clean and clear of any buildup! If you do these simple steps, you wonu2019t have any problems!!!!'),
(5398, 4, 1, 1, '2015-11-05', 'Ordered this as a gift for my daughter. It ... Ordered this as a gift for my daughter.  It was delivered the afternoon before she had to leave for Europe, and it wasn\'t opened until she got back, so she missed the return deadline.  Sadly, when she tried to use it for the first time, nothing worked - no light, no heat, no response whatsoever.  She tried different plugs in her apartment, etc., but that didn\'t work either.  We will never buy another product from Cuisinart!  Don\'t buy this toaster oven!'),
(5399, 7, 3, 4, '2015-06-08', 'Good price, simple to operate'),
(5400, 3, 1, 4, '2015-10-02', 'Four Stars I like, over my expectations!'),
(5401, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-15', 'review you can use the older kcups with this machine they are not compatable. warms quickly.  brews much quicker than older keurig Thanks Keurig for Free pods for this review'),
(5402, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-03', 'My Daughter Got this for Me to Replace a Bigger Coffee Machine that I had since I only Drink 1-2 cups a Day Now...Well..1st thing this morning I go and fix Reg. Ground Coffee & I thought maybe next time I will use more coffee since it was very weak & That was with 2 Tbls...But I Decided to Use a K-Cup..(Only to find out that My Machine was Missing the Pack Holder that goes in the Machine)...So I called HB Customer Service & was told that I would have to send in a Receipt in order to get the part...or Pay $5.99 + S&H for the K-Cup Pack Holder...Ok then I told her I had got The Donut House Brand K-Cup to use in the Machine...Only to be Informed that the Brand I Have WILL NOT WORK WITH THEIR MACHINE...Oh..And Not only this Brand...But a LIST OF OTHERS THAT WILL NOT WORK EITHER...So Before You Buy Make sure You have a List of the K-Cups that this Little Machine Can Use...Which is not many to me...Going to Return ASAP to the nearest Walmart that is 45 mins away...And will Get a Brand that Would Send You a Missing 5.99 part...esp. after finding out the K-Cups you just spend another $15+ on Will Not Work Either...Plus a 1 1/2 hr round trip drive...Very Frustrated at HB...'),
(5403, 3, 1, 4, '2015-03-31', 'Good Buy excellent! takes a little practice to work all features'),
(5404, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-27', 'I like it! It\'s my best toaster of pizza and bread.'),
(5405, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Our new favorite brewer! We just bought the K250 and love it. We originally bought it to take on trips as a second brewer to our K450. When we used it on an anniversary trip, we had decided it\'s going to be our everyday brewer now. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(5406, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-20', 'Great toaster for the money Very nice and stylish toaster oven with plenty of settings. It surely doesn\'t have all the bells and whistles of the more expensive models, but it solidly does it\'s job. Bread never comes out burned. Cleaning is a bit tricky as due to the construction of the door, crumbs are always left in the gap, but small hand vacuum helps. My only concern (-1 star) is that if the dial is set to a larger value, there is no way to reset it, and you have to wait till it comes to the desired position.'),
(5407, 6, 1, 3, '2015-09-25', 'Cheaply made I rated this with 3 stars because it is so cheaply made.  That said, most things today are cheaply made.  So this toaster works but it has issues, as well.  It only toasts one side of the bread, so it has to be watched closely and pushed up with cancel button so it won\'t burn.  Don\'t they test these products?  Cuisinart used to be a name with a good reputation.  I should have listened to the other reviews and saved my money.'),
(5408, 5, 1, 1, '2016-09-01', 'Do not buy this product if you want to program when it makes coffee. Easily broken. I am extremely disappointed in this coffeemaker. As a whole, it works just fine. However, the hour button on the auto programmable option is dysfunctional and broken. So now we have no way of programming the coffeemaker, and that was the whole point of purchasing a drip coffeemaker. I would not recommend this product to anyone.'),
(5409, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-30', 'thank you for a great product Amazon I\'m really enjoying this toaster oven along with my adult son..thank you for a great product Amazon!'),
(5410, 3, 1, 4, '2014-12-19', 'Perfect for me I read the other reviews before buying this and the most common complaint is the outside temperature. It does get hot; you won\'t instantly burn yourself by touching it but it\'s hot enough you can\'t leave your hand on it. That being said, I have a plastic coffee maker next to it along with a toaster with rubber feet on top and neither have melted down. This is my first toaster oven so I can\'t compare the performance with others. I can say that I\'m happy with the cook times and the convection feature.'),
(5411, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-29', 'Small, economical and gets the job done. Just the right size, I like the timer which alerts you when done.'),
(5412, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'Would buy this oven again as  it has all the features I wanted I had a specific list of features that I wanted in my oven and this model had them all. I also took a chance and purchased mine from the used category, but it was pretty much like new, and didn\'t appear to be used at all.  There were a couple of very slight dents on the top, but they were relatively unnoticeable unless you were looking for them at an angle.  You can\'t beat the price as it was 50% off the regular retail.  It came with a tray and roasting drip pan, which was a plus since I won\'t have to purchase them separately.  It can be difficult to gauge the size of an item from looking at a picture even when they provide you the measurements.  This is quite a large toaster convection oven, and is very roomy inside. Yet, it\'s not very heavy so I can easily move it around.  The front door drops down completely.  It does not have one of those hinges that automatically close (retract). Personally, I love the digital readouts because they are easier for me to see and this one is larger than some of the others.  I can\'t comment on temperature accuracy at this time, but I ordered an oven thermometer so I can check the temperature to make sure it\'s accurate.  I didn\'t buy this oven for cooking food although I may just buy another for the kitchen.  I plan to use it for polymer clay crafts, and temperature accuracy is a must have.  Nonetheless, it has to be better than my gas oven as I\'m always fiddling with the dial to try at get it at the right temperature.  I love having the timer and auto-shut-off feature because I get busy and forget.  The one thing I didn\'t like was a very short power cord.  I\'m not sure why they would do this, but the product manual stated that they made it shorter to prevent the cord from getting entangled or tripping over a longer cord.  Not sure how someone could trip over it if its up ion a counter.  If you are thinking about buying this oven you need to consider whether they have a space on the counter near an electrical outlet or use a heavy duty grounded extension.  As mentioned by others the exterior does get very hot, but I had the same issue with my Delonghi Toaster Convection Oven so I\'m used to protecting my hands, and keeping other items way from the oven when in use.  I keep my oven mitts next to the oven to remind me to use them whenever I use the oven.  The stainless steel exterior is quite nice looking, and has stylish curves.  I think that the top of the oven will be subject to dents as the metal seem a little thin on top.  I wouldn\'t be putting things on top, which you shouldn\'t anyway because of the heat issues.  The crumb tray slides in underneath the door so you don\'t have to open the oven to clean the tray.  I haven\'t quite decided whether this is good  idea or not.  The one thing that comes to mind if something is too large to fit through the crumb tray opening it could fall off on the oven floor.  However I like having a removable crumb tray to keep the oven clean.  There are four glass tube heating elements in this oven, and they are quite large compared to my Delonghi, which was four metal tubes not much thicker that my chopsticks in diameter.  Price wise it made more sense to buy a toaster convection oven because it does so much more.  The size of this oven allows you to cook just about anything.  I can cook a casserole, roast a chicken, and bake as well.  My daughter already baked her brownies, and they came out perfect.  Overall, I love this oven, and would buy it again.'),
(5413, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-17', 'the pot is easy to clean and there\'s nothing fancy that can easily ... For $12 there is no reason not to get this. It works exactly how you\'d expect. I don\'t get coffee grounds in my coffee and it tastes as it should. It brews 5 cups in right around 10 minutes, the pot is easy to clean and there\'s nothing fancy that can easily break. I bought one for home and one for work.'),
(5414, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-02', 'Five Stars good service and good buy'),
(5415, 5, 1, 3, '2015-11-29', 'If it\'s not in their perfect you\'ll have coffee everywhere Only use I\'ve had is you have to be careful putting the coffee pot into the machine. If it\'s not in their perfect you\'ll have coffee everywhere. It\'s happened to me a few times now. Never happened with any other machine. It\'s annoying but you just have to pay attention a little close with this machine.'),
(5416, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-18', 'Might be the best toaster oven for the price Might be the best toaster oven for the price. Controls work well, attractive on the counter, cooks well even with only one heat rod on the top. This surprised me that one upper rod worked, but it performs OK. A very good purchase, especially considering price.'),
(5417, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-16', 'Great for casual use PROS: **Available re-usable k-cup **Available carafe for larger brew sizes **Fast brew **Stylish look **Great for one cup of decaf or hot cocoa CONS: **I\'m not a fan of having to buy the k-cups.  I know that you can buy a reusable cup but that is an additional cost. **Only makes a 10oz cup of coffee without buying the additional carafe. **I like that you have the option of using a carafe but am not a huge fan of buying it separately. I like the machine - it looks great and works great.  As a steady drinker of at minimum 16oz of coffee in the morning with a spouse that drinks the same it doesn\'t look like it will ever be our daily brewer.  Awesome option of brewing into a carafe - maybe we need to cut our coffee consumption back :) ***Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review*** ***I received this product free for testing purposes***'),
(5418, 2, 1, 2, '2015-07-30', 'Does the job, but they product design flaws irk me It does what i expect of it in regards to cooking, and all the right cook settings are here. But there are three product design things I really dislike and make me suspect that either B&D didn\'t user test this unit or the engineers pushed it to production while the UX team was on vacation. 1. The chassis gets extremely hot on the outside. It needs an insulation layer to prevent accidentally touching the hot surface and getting a minor burn. 2. When setting the timer for something under 10 minutes, the instructions say to first turn the timer past 10 minutes and then back down to the desired time. If you don\'t do the extra dial, your food overcooks at the specified setting. My wife refuses to do the pre-requisite turn, and as a workaround sets the cook time to shorter than normal. 3. The control dials are gumdrop shaped and have a white radius line on the face to indicate which setting the dial is set to. Pretty standard design for control knobs, but the problem is the gumdrop shape and height of the knobs - unless the toaster oven is at eye level, the perspective of where the line points to and the actual setting is deceiving. To remedy, I used a white sharpie pen and extended a vertical line down from the edge of the existing white line of the knob face to the stainless steel.'),
(5419, 9, 1, 3, '2015-12-04', 'What you see is not what you get.... This coffee maker ad is deceptive.  They use a measurement of 5 oz, for a cup of coffee!  Who drinks a 5 oz. cup of coffee????  Most of us use mugs.  If I had know that, I may not have purchased this product.  Will have to use it more to see if I like it better.'),
(5420, 11, 1, 5, '2015-04-08', 'Five Stars I love all my items. Thank you Amazon'),
(5421, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-17', 'Great toaster oven LOVE this toaster! Saves me a ton of space by combining two appliances into one. I have had no issues with it.'),
(5422, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-17', 'Perfect! You do need either paper filters or buy ... Perfect! You do need either paper filters or buy a filament filter separately. It\'s perfect for two people. Or one person who likes two BIG cups of coffee. It\'s a pretty quick process once you\'ve turned it on.  NOTE: you must turn it off otherwise it WILL stay on all day.'),
(5423, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'Five Stars Very convenient and easy to use!'),
(5424, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-30', 'Five Stars Exactly what I wanted'),
(5425, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-21', 'This little guy is great for making single smoothies or sauces This little guy is great for making single smoothies or sauces. One of the best purchases I have made for my kitchen.'),
(5426, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-08', 'Awesome Possum!! I had a Mr. Coffee coffee maker that really didn\'t do the coffee justice. But this item really brings out the flavor in the coffee, especially over the time span i\'ve had this thing. Its been about a year and this coffee maker is still going strong with everyday use!!'),
(5427, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-16', 'Works great for all my toasting needs Sleek and modern look.  Works great for all my toasting needs.  We actually made enchiladas in here the other day and they turned out great.  My only complaint is that the chord is way too small!'),
(5428, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Great Toaster Oven Love this little oven. Use it more than my microwave. And in place of my large oven.'),
(5429, 4, 1, 4, '2016-08-02', 'Four Stars Nice little oven. Easy to use and reliable.'),
(5430, 5, 1, 4, '2015-06-28', 'Good value coffee maker Tried Kurieg and Bunn and disliked them both.  This works well, it\'s easy to use and clean, and produces consistently good coffee.  Can\'t beat it for the price.'),
(5431, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'I was definitely NOT disappointed. The ability to instantly make a cup of ... After much thought, I decided to purchase the Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing System. I was definitely NOT disappointed. The ability to instantly make a cup of coffee OR 4 cups worth of coffee using the carafe option is amazing and extremely convenient. In addition, being able to have instant access to hot water is really awesome. The product is well made and extremely sturdy. It is very easy to maintain and you will not be disappointed. Thanks, Keurig, for an amazing product. Also, thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review. What an awesome deal.'),
(5432, 5, 1, 4, '2016-06-23', 'Four Stars Rather noisy but coffee is good'),
(5433, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-03', 'Toaster owen I love it got on time.Faster than I assumed. Great product.'),
(5434, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-30', 'Five Stars I highly recommend this coffee make.  Works great.  The removable water tank is one of the best features.'),
(5435, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-14', 'I read all the reviews before buying, found no surprises. Just don\'t overfill it, or you\'ll get some extra steaming. It\'s been getting a real workout and still haven\'t needed the paperclip. The entire family is loving it. I usually run a 10 ounce cup followed by an extra 4 ounces for my travel cup, with most brand name coffee\'s this works well and gives a excellent cup of coffee, no weakness at all, some experimentation on your part and you will be very happy about all the money you saved over the BIG brand. READ and FOLLOW the instructions and you will love it.'),
(5436, 1, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'Awesome, Simple system, Brews Great Coffee! Very simple to use system, easy to use, easy to clean, brews great coffee!!! \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(5437, 5, 1, 3, '2016-12-24', 'It would be 5 stars if: I love everything about this machine except it does not brew at the advertised 200 degrees.  Mine brews at about 160, I\'m thinking about exchanging it! The \"no-drip\" feature is brilliant and the removable water tank is very convenient.  It is also super easy to program.'),
(5438, 4, 1, 5, '2017-01-07', 'Would buy it again. Lives up to billing.'),
(5439, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-05', 'KEURIG K200 Absolutely LOVE LOVE LOVE IT.  What a phenomenal upgrade from the original Keurig. Delicious coffee! The carafe is a MAJOR PLUS.. I brew a carafe k-cup and take the carafe with me to work. I couldn\'t be happier with this product. LOVE IT!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(5440, 3, 1, 1, '2016-06-15', 'This unit is terrible to use and the broiler still does not work ... This unit is terrible to use and the broiler still does not work (will not stay on broil) after trying for almost 2 years now.'),
(5441, 5, 1, 3, '2015-03-20', 'Makes very hot coffee which we live but it tends ... Makes very hot coffee which we live but it tends to be very noisy while it is brewing. My old coffee maker kept the coffee hot for 4 hours this coffee pot only keeps it hot for 2.'),
(5442, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-27', 'I love it. It\'s easy to clean I love it. It\'s easy to clean, toasts well, and can even make my bagel pizzas or just two cookies without heating up the whole house.'),
(5443, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-02', 'This is a great size for personal use and also for beginner blender ... This is a great size for personal use and also for beginner blender users.  I had a full sized blender years ago and it was such a pain to use and a bigger hassle to clean, left it with my ex and never missed it.  I got this one recently as a gift and I use it nearly every day to make many different drinks.  The size is perfect for a single serving or for two servings.  It takes up little room on the counter and is each to move around or store away and get back out again.  It\'s simple to use and even easier to clean, which came as a pleasant surprise.  If you are looking for one with multiple settings or one that will not leave chunks in the blend, then this is not the blender for you, but this works great for simple users such as myself.'),
(5444, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-14', 'Love this blender Great personal blender.  I like if I\'m in a rush I can use the travel cup or otherwise transfer my drink to another travel cup.  I would recommend using crushed ice or smaller pieces since the blades aren\'t too big.  I haven\'t had any trouble, that is just my recommendation.'),
(5445, 9, 1, 1, '2016-03-02', 'I could get better from a 39 I purchased this coffeemaker in June 2015. I would never purchase another, there is no way to keep it hot. I had go out and purchase a thermal carafe to transfer coffee after brewing. Mine is a total joke. Not worth the money I spent, I could get better from a 39.00 pot.......'),
(5446, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-07', 'This coffee maker has some pretty nice features This coffee maker has some pretty nice features. I\'m not a fan of super hot coffee. I like how this maker lets me pick the temp of the warmer. The timer feature is great do. Nothing like waking up to that folgers in your cup.  Know what I mean?.'),
(5447, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Love this blender I love this blender. I\'ve used it basically everyday for over 1 year. It just crapped out on me yesterday. The razor blade in the jar separated from the bottom of the jar and my shake spilled out from underneath all over the counter. Thankfully I have a backup blender. I felt like I got my money\'s worth based on how much I used this. It was the perfect size, small, compact and blended my shakes to a perfect consistency. Will absolutely buy again!'),
(5448, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-12', 'Five Stars Great price and great quality.'),
(5449, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-14', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(5450, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-09', 'This is my second one. First one lasted over ... This is my second one.  First one lasted over 5 years and I use it almost every day.'),
(5451, 3, 1, 1, '2016-05-28', 'One Star Item started smoking badly upon first use. Unfortunately, we are sending it back.'),
(5452, 7, 3, 5, '2014-06-22', 'I got this for my husband because he has been wanting a k-cup but the cost of the actual k-cup coffee maker is super expensive this costs less and works just as well. It is very user friendly and does not take up a lot of space as a traditional coffee maker I would recommend this to anyone.'),
(5453, 3, 1, 3, '2016-08-21', 'Three Stars So far so good.'),
(5454, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-18', 'works well Works well and price is right.'),
(5455, 2, 1, 3, '2015-11-18', 'top gets a bit hot, but it works top gets hot and I miss the feature that pulls the tray out as the door is pulled open, but it works and works well'),
(5456, 3, 1, 1, '2015-11-21', 'Catches fire Catches fire.....totally clean oven catches fire. Also catches fire if pizza cheese drips on heating coil. Not safe.'),
(5457, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-29', 'I love this Hamilton Beach coffee maker. It uses standard k cups or ground coffee and you can make 3 different size brews: 8 oz, 10 oz, and 14 oz cups. It also has two brew settings regular or bold which works well and is a nice feature. The K cup holder can be removed to reveal a reusable, washable screen to use to brew regular loose ground coffee. Which is another great feature. The base of the pot can be raised to accommodate a small cup or lower it to use a travel mug. This coffee maker can brew a cup of coffee as fast or faster than any Keurig brewer. For those energy conscious folks this brewer doesn\'t continuously heat water. It heats only when the brew button is pushed. You need to fill the cup size you want with water and then pour it into the top and the place the cup on the base. Add a K cup or ground coffee and the push the brew button. This is a terrific product and I highly recommend it.'),
(5458, 5, 1, 1, '2016-10-22', 'Well, it died after just 5 weeks. My husband and I initially purchased one of these a few years ago, and it lasted for about 3 years. I was cool with this since it is a reasonably priced product. We decided to get another one when the first one died. The second one had a missing bezel, so Hamilton Beach sent us another. The third one died this morning. It is dead and won\'t turn on. I am disappointed since it seems that this coffee maker has gone down hill in the past few years.'),
(5459, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'No problems ! Good little toaster. Compact and works well for small space'),
(5460, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'Works Great Very good.'),
(5461, 7, 3, 4, '2015-01-02', 'I have only been using this for a week but so far so good. The price was good. I like that I can use ground coffee as well as the k cups. The only problem that I am having is when I use the ground coffee, it has a bitter, gritty taste in the last sip. Not sure what I am doing wrong.'),
(5462, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Bought it for my 83yr old Mother to replace her ... Bought it for my 83yr old Mother to replace her blender for smoothies in the morning. She Loves it!! :)'),
(5463, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-20', 'Five Stars Fits nicely in small kitchen.'),
(5464, 5, 1, 4, '2016-07-30', 'Very convenient Most convenient coffee maker I have ever used. Coffee  not as hot as I would like, but I usually reheat in the microwave before I finish a cup anyway.'),
(5465, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-21', 'Combo Toaster/Oven This is my second Toastation and we love it.  I was so happy to find it still available after so long.  Pretty sure our first one was about, at least, 10 years old.'),
(5466, 1, 1, 4, '2016-09-23', 'This is a nice machine. What is annoying This is a nice machine. What is annoying, as others have stated, is there are times when you need to keep opening and shutting the top in order to get it working. This is not a huge deal really. This is still a great device to have.'),
(5467, 7, 3, 1, '2015-12-16', 'I have had this coffee maker for about a month. It worked really well and I was pleased with it. But it quit working. It goes through all the motions and you can hear the water heating but no water comes out. If you buy this product be sure to keep your receipt.'),
(5468, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-06', 'Awesome product for your buck! For the price it\'s fantastic! Now I suggest to freeze or use frozen fruit for a thick smoothie. One of the things I love about this product is you can use the same cup to drink out of so you aren\'t having to clean up much. If using ice, I suggest crushed ice, I only have cubes so I put two cubes and blend them till nice and crushed before adding my fruit and milk. Trust me I learned the hard way and discovered that way gives the best results. Also it is very important you are careful and hold the blender in place, if you don\'t you will smell a funky smell and can ruin your new blender. I think it works well, but you must take care of it!'),
(5469, 2, 1, 3, '2015-07-11', 'It\'s ok, but it burns all our toast I\'ve had this toaster for a few months now and still have yet to make a good piece of toast. I constantly burn up all the toast with this thing. So does everyone else in my family. The problem is the knob that sets the time and darkness level--it\'s just not easy to put it where it should be, it\'s stiff and impossible to really read where it is. So the toast option is aggravating, however, using broil or bake works fine. It just seems to run a bit hot and must be watched. The price was good, I didn\'t have money to put out on a really nice toaster, so this will do until I have 70 bucks or so for a more user friendly one.'),
(5470, 7, 3, 4, '2015-08-08', 'I really like this single serve coffee maker. It makes hot coffee fast & I can use pods or grounds.'),
(5471, 6, 1, 3, '2015-06-11', 'I am somewhat disappointed with this toaster I am somewhat disappointed with this toaster.  It does not toast the same on both sides; one side is always darker than the other side.  Since Cuisinart is a popular name brand, I would think that this toaster would have been made to toast the same color on BOTH sides.  I consider this toaster substandard.  A less expensive toaster would more than likely toast better than this one!'),
(5472, 2, 1, 3, '2015-06-18', 'Ok if you can make the timer work Nice features and the unit is small enough to fit in our spot.  However, the timer knob leaves a lot to be desired.  It turns very hard and it is impossible to set at the same spot twice.  Our old Black & Decker had a handy push down lever that always worked the same.  We sold this oven at a garage sale and bought a Cuisinart.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(5473, 5, 1, 4, '2016-09-28', 'Good performance, but don\'t let the carafe pop out and break! Nothing remarkable, but solid.  Reasonably fast, reasonably quiet, reasonably convenient (the coffee basket swings out).  Useful settings for modifying the brewing conditions (small pot, more bold, temperature of the carafe).  Little wheels are perfect for allowing easy motion on the counter, but it does not move during brewing/without a shove.  The only downside is that insertion of the carafe into the brewer requires an intentional shove.  Fail to do that and it pops out and, maybe, falls off the counter and breaks.  And the replacement carafe must be exact (no generics) and is expensive/hard to find.  Not speaking from experience or anything...'),
(5474, 1, 1, 4, '2016-02-23', 'Pour it on! This was a present for the office and has been a big hit.'),
(5475, 12, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Five Stars Works great, still using it after all this time.'),
(5476, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-05', 'Awesome product! Its an awesome product! I loved it.. Its so cute product, easy to carry when out on travel, picnic, office, smaller size, makes hardly any nice while mixing/blending fruits, dry fruits etc. The best part is the jar is BPA free and it makes it easy to carry shake/juice in same jar.. So no hastle to fill in the shake in other bottle. Saves time! In love with this product. I would definitely recommend this product.'),
(5477, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Great little toaster oven at a great price I\'ve been using this toaster oven for over a year now and I have 0 complaints. It\'s definitely little (you can fit about 2 medium slices of pizza in comfortably at a time) but I\'ve never been frustrated with the size and it works well for my small apartment. I highly recommend.'),
(5478, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-01', 'Good Oven Got this to bake my polymer clay pieces in thinking it would be perfect for it.  The oven itself is GREAT and works like a charm but unfortunately it is not tall enough for most of my pieces and a bit too little.  :(  Oh well, it is not the products fault, in fact, as I said the oven is nice just not what I wanted it for. :)'),
(5479, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'I Am In LOVE With This Keurig!!!! So yesterday my Keurig2.0 K200 came in! I am enjoying it! I have already brewed a Swiss Miss Hot Chocolate and a Celestial Seasonings English Breakfast Black Tea! Just so you know there are more than 400 different beverages from 60 brands! Starbucks, Lipton, Swiss Miss and Dunkin\' Donuts are just a few of the brands that you can find for Keurig! You can go to www.keurig.com for a full list of the brands! So let me tell you about the Keurig2.0 K200! This model holds 40 ounces of water in its reservoir! It has customizable options so you can brew 4, 6, 8 or 10 ounces or fill a carafe! Another option is strength control if you feel like a bolder cup of coffee. It also has a setting for your hot chocolates, mochas or other specialty beverages! It has the Keurig2.0 brewing technology which means if it doesnt say KEURIG BREWED on the seal it will not brew it. That is a downfall to some who want to buy generic brands. This model is available in seven colors! So if you work for let\'s say Westwood ISD home of the Panthers a Orange Zest would look awesome in your office or classroom! Overall I am very satisfied with this machine! **I did receive this product free for testing.**'),
(5480, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'Cuisinart DCC-3000 Coffee-on-Demand 12-Cup... I purchased this refurbished carafe- less coffee maker based on price versus cost of new. I am completely satisfied with the purchase. I have used it in all modes, auto brew, brew, and adjustable off. Every thing works as intended, no buyers remorse. I have the auto shutoff set for one hour, coffee left in machine doesn\'t get any burned flavor to it in that amount of time. More machine than I was looking for but price was right.'),
(5481, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-30', 'Relaly like it! It works great and we are really pleased with it.  The only thing that I would recommend is that they put a longer than 2 hour warming period.  Otherwise, would buy it again anytime.'),
(5482, 7, 3, 5, '2016-07-24', 'I\'m happy with the design. Easy to clean. No standing water inside the machine. Drip tray is easy to take off and clean. Very happy!'),
(5483, 8, 1, 5, '2015-11-12', 'Five Stars Wonderful product! Makes the best tasting coffee.'),
(5484, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-02', 'I received the Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffee Maker, I can\'t say enough about it! There are a variety of ways to make your favorite coffee or tea: one way is regular ground coffee or teabags goes into the basket, or you can use a coffee pod, or finally you can use the popular K-Cups are easily inserted into the removable slide-in tray. To allow for two sizes of coffee cups, the lower portion of the unit lets you place either a large travel mug on top, or flip it over for a higher ledge to place a smaller mug. Water in the back, press the button, and within minutes you\'re drinking a hot cup of coffee or tea! Realizing it\'s only a single cup machine makes it perfect for me being single. I love how quickly you clean up, a simple rinse of the grinds from the basket and you\'re set for the next cup. Instructions say to run a solution of 1/2 cup white vinegar and 1/2 cup water through the unit every month or so to clean it out. This makes more sense than the more costly machines that require descaling and fancy solutions in order to keep the coffee tasting great. It\'s a tall and thin machine, so you easily slide it beside other kitchen appliances without taking up much counter space. Black and stainless steel finish go with everything. I have other Hamilton Beach kitchen appliances and honestly have not been disappointed yet. This coffee maker is a keeper!'),
(5485, 11, 1, 4, '2015-04-26', 'Good small toaster oven. We replaced a 15 year old similar model of same brand that finally gave up after much good service. Like the old model better: this one is fatter front-to-back than it has to be, but most others now are even FATTER without more cooking space. Toasts, bakes, broils well. Built a lot lighter than the old one, but isn\'t everything? Can anyone recommend a quality toaster oven for really limited counter space, mainly shallow front-to-back? Didn\'t see much modern style that was smaller than this.'),
(5486, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love my new brewer! After several years of use my first Keurig gave up the ghost.  I bought myself the 2.0 and I love it!  I enjoy having the option of 10oz when making my coffee by the cup since I am not a fan of strong coffee.  The only draw back has been that you cannot use KCups that are not specifically labeled Keurig.  I had some tea, that I loved, and am not able to use it and cannot find a similar flavor with the Keurig brand.  I am pleased that the unit shuts itself off in an hour if not used.  My husband worries about me leaving the unit on, so that concern is now relieved.  Thanks Keurig for two free boxes of coffee for this honest review.'),
(5487, 4, 1, 1, '2015-01-13', 'Fire and Electrocution Hazard! Apart from that... After 2 1/2 years the lower front heating element has completely warped, and will likely soon break. It also sits on top of a microwave oven, and if your hand makes contact between the outer casing of the microwave and the toaster oven when the toaster is on, you get an electric shock! Many other customers are reporting the same issue (re: the heating element, not the mild electrocution). This product is clearly defective and should undergo a safety recall. However, the company apparently only offers a replacement under warranty, at the cost of a new toaster. So unless you are interested in spending $25/year on toaster ovens, and risking your life, you may want to consider another toaster oven. Preferably not one from Cuisinart.'),
(5488, 11, 1, 4, '2014-12-02', 'good toaster, good price, easy to clean Very compact, so it won\'t take up a lot of counter space. It has surprisingly good power, putting up high temperatures quickly, and a broad range of cooking options compared to other toaster ovens in its price range. One knock, is that there is a deceivingly short distance between the cooking tray and the top heating coil is VERY SMALL. You can\'t really get a New York style bagel in there unless it\'s cut in half. That is something to keep in mind when you consider your needs in your toaster oven choice.'),
(5489, 2, 1, 3, '2016-09-20', 'Black & decker toaster oven Print for knobs to small to read. To many steps to just toast  broil or bake. Not user friendly Liked my GE one better.'),
(5490, 7, 3, 1, '2014-01-06', 'When I first got the coffee maker, sounded almost too good to be true.....it was! Pour in water get about half the amount back into the cup, second time I used it water came out clear and most shot all over the place, but the kcup was punctured. I put it back in its box and returned it! Don\'t waste your time'),
(5491, 5, 1, 3, '2016-01-26', 'not to happy with the quality of material it is made of not to happy with the quality of material it is made of. The filter compartment is not closing correctly.  I am not a coffee drinker. what was important for me was that my husband would be happy with the coffee maker.  husband is ok with it.'),
(5492, 4, 1, 2, '2015-11-18', 'I have had this toaster oven about 2 years and ... I have had this toaster oven about 2 years and 3 times it has had scary malfunctions.  All three times I was in the kitchen and thankfully a fire did not break our.  The heating elements shoot up to the highest level and then it will not cut off unless I unplug it from the wall.  My slow toasting pecans at 200 degrees burned up in about 10 minutes because the heating elements were so hot.  When I came over and saw what was happening I turned the knob to off and then opened the door and all this smoke came rushing out and the heating elements continued to stay on at an extremely high temperature,( I am guessing broiling temperature).  I checked the off switch and then unplugged the toaster so the heat would stop.  Dangerous for any house!!!'),
(5493, 5, 1, 4, '2015-01-18', 'Four Stars Works great!'),
(5494, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Five Stars Purchased this for my wife so she could.put it in her office. She loves the it.'),
(5495, 3, 1, 5, '2015-11-10', 'Replaced this for an older model and so happy I did Replaced this for an older model and so happy I did. Works great and buttons are more functional, just harder to read.'),
(5496, 6, 1, 4, '2015-06-04', 'It works good! The only part that doesn\'t is when I ... It works good! The only part that doesn\'t is when I select the Bagel option. When I do all the heating elements on both sides burns bright toasting all sides of the bagel. Fortunately I don\'t eat bagels much.'),
(5497, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-07', 'Five Stars Great.'),
(5498, 12, 1, 4, '2014-09-10', 'Four Stars Works good, but the tray should have a non-stick coating.'),
(5499, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-12', 'awesome product this product is just awesome, toast bread in few minute, even browning. I got this product within 3 days ... I am using this for almost 15 days ,,, no problem'),
(5500, 6, 1, 3, '2016-03-04', 'it works but like so many toasters it always toasts one side of ... it works but like so many toasters it always toasts one side of the bread just a wee bit better'),
(5501, 3, 1, 1, '2016-10-04', 'Too bad. Maybe I\'ll try buying another one Was never operational. Plugged it in all over the house and it never powered up. Amazon took it back for a refund. Too bad. Maybe I\'ll try buying another one, but not for a while.'),
(5502, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-16', 'Easy to clean Easy to clean, fits in my SUV\'s cupholder, and blends really well! I\'m actually going to purchase another one.'),
(5503, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-13', 'Great compact package and simple functionality make it easy to use. Second one I have had, lost the other in the breakup. Works like a champ. I love its compact size and simple functionality.'),
(5504, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'Good Morning Really like this little coffee maker.  I had a four cup Krups coffee maker for years; but since when they say four cups, they really mean one and a quarter cups.  This one said five cups, which really does make two nice big cups.  For a solo person, this is just fine, especially if you don\'t want to pay a hundred dollars for the individual cup makers.  If you really want the best tasting coffee, use bottled water, not tap.'),
(5505, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-22', 'Very Satisfied. Good quality and very happy with this purchase as it heats up foods and toasts perfectly to my liking.  Looks nice on counter and compliments the kitchen\'s decor..'),
(5506, 3, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'this is wonderful! Easy cleaning On those hot summer days, when you want something in the oven, and do not want to use the stove oven, this is wonderful! Easy cleaning, easy to use, love it!'),
(5507, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'A delight to use Superb coffee maker!  It looks great, and I particularly enjoy the visible, removable water reservoir that I can take to the kitchen faucet and the LED light that shows me how much coffee I have in the cup I am filling.  We have used two previous models of this carafe-less model and enjoyed those, too.  However, these models seem to have a useful life that barely exceeds the limited warranty.  My pleasure in using this particular model is delightful enough as to justify buying another one at the current price if it quits working.'),
(5508, 3, 1, 5, '2014-06-25', 'Does a really good job... a 12\" pizza DOES fit!  It did not come with a manual, which is weird, but easy enough to look up online.  I did that since it is not super intuitive how to use some of the features.  Quality.'),
(5509, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-05', 'Easy to use Hamilton Beach 46201 Great coffee maker.  Wanted a nice sleek design to go with the rest of my black/stainless appliances.  Does not take up much room on the counter.  The under-neath wheels make it easy to just spin around to access the water re-fill compartment that easily is removed to bring to your sink to fill up.  No more spilling water on the counter while trying to pour water into the devise.  No reason to even pull the unit out from beneath the cabinets.  Still trying to master the morning auto timer though.  It has a 1-4 cup setting which is a nice feature.  Highly recommend!'),
(5510, 12, 1, 2, '2016-03-09', 'Functional, cheap, bad warranty. Broke after 6 months. Nice small size for a multi purpose device. The company wants $12 to ship me a replacement one after I mail the broken unit back or take a photo of it with the cord cut.'),
(5511, 5, 1, 4, '2014-07-07', 'Great machine. Stupid sticker they put on the front ... Great machine. Stupid sticker they put on the front left a residue mark on the stainless steel.  Would be a 5 if it wasnt for the sticker mark.'),
(5512, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-02', 'Got it as a gift for people who aren\'t tiresome coffee snobs but enjoy a good cup Got it as a gift for people who aren\'t tiresome coffee snobs but enjoy a good cup.  They love it.'),
(5513, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-25', 'Smart looking, practical, and awesomely simplistic and effective. I love this!!!! No nonsense with a nicely crafted coffee pot. Sleek looking and makes a good cup of joe without a lot of space (and it doesn\'t look to small).'),
(5514, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'Five Stars Perfect toaster)'),
(5515, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-09', 'I like it We use it every day and it Is working well. Very satisfied.'),
(5516, 12, 1, 5, '2016-09-12', 'They love it. This was a gift for my son and his family.  They love it.'),
(5517, 9, 1, 1, '2015-02-16', 'I have enjoyed my old Cuisinart but the toggle switch broke again The coffee is just not strong enough to suit my taste. I have enjoyed my old Cuisinart but the toggle switch broke again. I am disappointed in this Cuisinart and would like to return it to Amazon.'),
(5518, 9, 1, 3, '2016-03-20', 'Great setup for cleaning. Didn\'t think it made a particularly great tasting brew. Maybe its my coffee? However, has less taste than my previous Braun machine produced. It makes as many cups as you put in in the water reserve. Have no idea why there is a 1-4 cup brew button. Made no obvious difference in the brew.  Love the setup. After done, can easily wash out the removable basket and removable coffee reservoir, which is below the basket. Important to us because she likes flavored and I do not. Have to wash it out to get rid of flavor taste! Now we have one machine for both of us.'),
(5519, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-02', 'Excellent Haven\'t had an issue at all. Toasts well.'),
(5520, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-24', 'Great item, great value! Very nice toaster. I\'ve had one of these before, and got another for my young adult daughter who will soon be moving into her own apartment. This is the best price I found as well.'),
(5521, 6, 1, 5, '2014-02-07', 'perfect Bought as a gift, and she says its perfect. fits the bagels great, toasts great, even has a defrost if her bagels are frozen. and she loves the empty tray.'),
(5522, 5, 1, 4, '2014-07-10', 'Easy to use, and customer service is good. My review is that the function is good.  It turns on when it\'s supposed to, and stays on for two hours at a time (though it\'s easy to use for longer periods by turning on and off quickly).  The clock is accurate, and it\'s easy to use and set in order to wake up to a fresh pot of coffee.  It was great while it lasted.  The only reason it is four stars is that it lasted less than one year (which was within warranty). It was easy to replace by calling Hamilton Beach, giving the model and series number, and sending them a photo with the plug cut off.  I did have to pay S&H, but it\'s considerably less than a new coffee maker. If it lasted fourteen months, I would have to buy a new coffee pot.  But it would be a bit over ten cents a day for a machine that has coffee ready when you get up.  Not bad when you look at it that way.  That said, I am hoping to get more usage out of the new one they send me.'),
(5523, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-02', 'Five Stars works great!'),
(5524, 5, 1, 1, '2015-04-29', 'Worked for six months! This was a great maker until it just topped working after only six months! The worst part was trying to deal with Hamilton Beach to honor their warranty. I won\'t buy another product of theirs because of that. They have horrible customer service. Good for Amazon for having the best customer service! They promptly refunded my money.'),
(5525, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-19', '... trying to find this coffee maker with all its great features. I love the pull out coffee basket ... I spent a day trying to find this coffee maker with all its great features.  I love the pull out coffee basket (removable) and removable water holder with clearly visible quantities.  This coffee maker is easy to use and program.  The coffee is great as well!  Great product for the price.  I\'m loving it.'),
(5526, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-05', 'Loved it, it\'s perfect for my herbal life shakes Loved it, it\'s perfect for my herbal life shakes. I love how you can drink it right out of the container.'),
(5527, 4, 1, 5, '2016-03-05', 'Five Stars This is a wonderful toaster. I just love it'),
(5528, 8, 1, 4, '2016-04-25', 'Great Little Coffee Maker for the Price This Black & Decker coffee maker may be entry level, but for the price you cannot miss. It gets the job done quickly and easily. It is easy to clean and will run for as long as you need it (unless you drop the carafe like I did and need a new one). In truth, I do not taste any difference between the expensive coffee makers and this.'),
(5529, 6, 1, 3, '2015-11-26', 'Not quite living up to expectations For the most part it is a pretty good toaster, but it has a few issues that would prevent me from buying it again. Namely, bread that is unusually small or thin tends to burn on one side. We have had it for less than a year and all the lettering is wearing off!'),
(5530, 12, 1, 4, '2015-09-10', 'Toaster & more Love the fact that it\'s a toaster & oven . The oven is a little small but for me it\'s ok'),
(5531, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Five Stars I\'m loving it!'),
(5532, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-10', 'Quite pleased, great value Works very well. Suprised at how well it toasted english muffins. Quite pleased, great value.'),
(5533, 12, 1, 2, '2015-09-12', 'Nice price, but limited utilty You might think it can toast bagels and cook in the oven part at the same time, but the bagels extend into the toaster oven part and you can\'t use both sections at the same time.'),
(5534, 9, 1, 4, '2015-12-02', 'good coffee, but difficult to read well, my husband loves it.  i prefer a one cup system, but, fresh ground beans and this coffee maker will wake you up with a smooth flavor and a good cup of coffee.  one suggestion ... make the markings white so that older eyes can see them.  black lettering isn\'t easily read.'),
(5535, 12, 1, 4, '2016-07-25', 'Works like champ! I\'ve had this toaster for a few years and it gets every day use. We like it. It works really well. I\'ve toasted bread and bagels both. Most breads you can fit side by side, although for some fat loaves you have to squeeze the two slices together. My only complaint is that there\'s no cancel button. If you want it to stop toasting, you have to unplug it. It doesn\'t work to try and flip up the lever. (unless I\'m a dummy and missed a really simple trick somewhere!). It\'s pretty easy to clean too... you just have to take out the tray inside every so often and toss the crumbs, and wash it. I almost never use the oven part, but maybe a couple of times a year. It works well. You have to flip a switch to close off the toaster opening for the oven to turn on. Works well when I\'ve used it.'),
(5536, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-23', '^ Showed up fast going to use it to temper steel in in the shop'),
(5537, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-16', 'Room enough for a 9X9 baking dish or casserole Great convection and regular oven, use it a lot to save running the big oven.'),
(5538, 2, 1, 2, '2016-09-21', 'I wish I could go back in time and buy something better! Toasts everything uneven! God forbid you cook a few frozen pizza\'s in in...burnt on one side, undercooked on the other. I wish I could go back in time and buy something better!.'),
(5539, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-14', 'Great little toaster oven! I\'ve never had a toaster oven before so I relied on reviews quite a bit when deciding which model to choose.  It needed to be fairly small because I hate to give up counter space, but I wanted it to be big enough to cook a decent amount.  I love this thing!  My main use is cooking chicken nuggets or fish sticks for my toddler but I\'ve also used it to reheat pizza or crisp up things like tater tots or french fries.  It\'s very easy to use and food turns out great!  I don\'t use it for toast because for some reason I always forget and burn my toast but I\'m sure if I actually paid attention it would be good for that as well.  As some other reviewers have said, the unit does get hot so don\'t leave anything on top of it or touching it when it\'s on.'),
(5540, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-28', 'Excellent and Easy to Use Really easy to use! Love the water reservoir on the back, and the rotating action base, pull out, rotate to back, slide plastic reservoir up and off the back to fill, then slide right back down onto the machine. Precludes a sleepy user from banging a glass coffee pot into the side of the sink because my eyes aren\'t quite open yet!'),
(5541, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-02', 'Love! I love that I can remove reservoir tank and take it to the sink to fill it! No more messes trying to pour water into a small opening!! My other favorite feature of this coffee pot is the easy access button, I love that I can hit a button and the basket swings out to load the coffee grounds. Very user friendly!'),
(5542, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-03', 'Four Stars It is a good blender. It is perfect to make small drinks, but not for large portions.'),
(5543, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Five Stars best toaster ever .'),
(5544, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-08', 'Five Stars i love it'),
(5545, 5, 1, 1, '2016-09-20', 'Started leaking coffee for no reason Started leaking coffee for no reason after a couple of months. A coffee pot should last longer than that. The coffee was so-so.'),
(5546, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-26', 'Five Stars Very good!.'),
(5547, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-24', 'Five Stars Really like this toaster. Its all they said it would be'),
(5548, 12, 1, 3, '2015-06-21', 'Great for toast Great for toast, but the oven part is very small and close to the heat source, so most things end up getting burned quickly.'),
(5549, 12, 1, 1, '2015-02-15', 'One Star Pretty cheap. No timer and very small.'),
(5550, 1, 1, 1, '2016-09-28', 'Honestly, there is no reason that a coffee machine ... Honestly, there is no reason that a coffee machine that costs the price this does should have maintenance issues after only 3 weeks of using. Your customer service representatives are helpful but it\'s not really an excuse for making a cheap product. I will continue to make you spend money by sending me replacements every time your unsatisfactory product breaks but I will never be buying from this company again.'),
(5551, 12, 1, 3, '2016-06-25', 'Top part works great, bottom part not well at all This is a great toaster, but the bottom section doesn\'t do anything right, so far as I can tell. I\'ve owned it for two years and I gave up trying to use the bottom after multiple disappointing attempts to access the services it was supposed to provide. Oh, well. Live and learn.'),
(5552, 5, 1, 3, '2015-11-18', 'Not Quite What We Wanted I do not like the glass container as much as a stainless steel dispenser.  My husband measured both of them and actually the temperatures of the coffee are the same. The real problem we have is that the last bit of coffee or the last bit of water when you wash out the carafe does not come out.  You have to twist and turn the glass container, upside down and inside out (if you could) but that little bit of coffee or water will not pour out of the dispenser. The other problem is that when you put in the descriptions, you can either put in Bold coffee or 1 to 4 cups of coffee.  When you press the button, you have a choice of Bold coffee or 1 to 4 cups of coffee.  Maybe someone can tell me why you need to indicate that you are going to make 1 to 4 cups of coffee.  My husband and I drink different brands of coffee so we have to make one cup at a time but we both indicate the Bold choice. Something else this coffee maker does not have is a beeper or signal to indicate the coffee is ready.  And you can hear the coffee drip long after the coffee is ready, so if you do not wait for awhile, you will not have eight ounces of coffee.'),
(5553, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-25', 'Great! No problems with it. Excellent and powerful.'),
(5554, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-28', 'Works well for all needs Great.  Everyone in our house of 5 use it daily and it works for toast, bagels, and the kids pop tarts.'),
(5555, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-10', 'Five Stars Best coffeemaker we\'ve ever had! We got rid of Keurig since they went to 2.0.'),
(5556, 11, 1, 5, '2014-12-14', 'Five Stars simple and adequate or actually very good as a toaster.  Have not used it as an oven.  Pleasant design.'),
(5557, 6, 1, 4, '2015-01-05', 'Enjoyed, until..... I would have given this 5 stars had I not had an issue with the right side.  After using this toaster several times, the right side will decide to lock down sometimes, and sometimes not.  I have a feeling it has something to do with the cancel button. (might be sticking).  Other than that, I love all the features.'),
(5558, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-20', 'Well-built and spacious toaster oven The weddings gifts are starting to arrive, and this Cuisinart Toaster Oven is the first! It features a range of settings to match you toasting/baking needs. We\'ve experiment with a few and have had good results all around. - DIMENSIONS - The Cuisinart Toaster Oven is a perfect size to tuck into a corner in our kitchen. It measures 16\" long and 11\" wide, so not too lengthy or wide that it takes up too much counter space. The baking sheet size is ideal for four slices of toast - not too cramped. You can probably fit a good size piece of leftover pizza in there as well...hmmmm might have to try that one! - COOKING - We\'ve mostly toasted bread and bagels. I struggled a bit at the beginning to find the perfect setting (the darker toast settings tend to make the toast a little crispy), but once I got a feel for the toast knob everything now toast just fine. We experimented with melting cheese to make quesadillas or filled pitas in the BAKE setting, and it worked perfectly! We used the broiler to make garlic bread using pitas, also worked like a charm. Overall a great product, very glad we added this to our registry!'),
(5559, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-23', 'Already love it after it arrived 3 days ago Already love it after it arrived 3 days ago. I have been using it ever since. It is stylish, as it is portable and easy to use. Already introduce it to friends, and they love it too. Get it!'),
(5560, 8, 1, 3, '2016-08-02', 'Three Stars Cheap but effective, works with the Mr Coffee 6659 gold filter.'),
(5561, 7, 3, 1, '2014-04-14', 'I bought this coffee maker to keep at work. It has been used a maximum of 5 times per week to brew decaf coffee and tea cups. I have tried different brands of cups and have only used bottled distilled water, as I do with all of my coffee makers. It is cheaply made and is very messy, spewing water and steam and coffee grounds every time it makes a cup. I first read and tried all the helpful hints in the user manual. Finally I called customer service; a rep walked me through the user manual and offered another suggestion to clean out the puncturing tool with a paper clip (which fills with grounds each time I brew a cup of coffee), which I attempted over the course of a few days. The second customer service rep told me I needed to use different k-cups and offered the same suggestions that did not yield different results. Like the first rep, I was made to feel that there was something I was or wasn\'t doing incorrectly or I wasn\'t caring for the coffee maker as I should be. Finally the rep told me that I could ship the product back to them (for nearly half the original price), as stated in the Limited Warrant section of the use guide. I should have read reviews before purchasing the product in the first place; I am opting to accept my losses and purchase a new single serve coffee maker of a different brand that doesn\'t require me to try to \"fix\" it with a paper clip then clean up the entire counter every time I want to brew a cup of coffee. My advice is to potential buyers is to spend a little bit more and purchase a product that works as advertised.'),
(5562, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-17', 'Works very well - best maker we have had Has simple controls but includes 3 levels of temperature control and 3 brewing strengths.  Tank pulls out the back or you can easily fill while in the unit.  We always pull the tank and fill it with water.  Seals look robust so it should last.  Simple paper filter tray that comes out so you can dump it.  Have not seen grounds splashing up, getting through or other issues.  Pouring is great, has an extra piece of plastic at the top of the craft that keeps the coffee from splashing open the lid and going all over and the lid doesn\'t flop open as you pour out the last bit of coffee.  Only issue is you might get a single drop from the filter valve onto the heater plate if you pull it out quickly.  Had it for a month of heavy use and it appears to be holding up well.'),
(5563, 6, 1, 4, '2016-07-27', 'Four Stars so far good product.'),
(5564, 6, 1, 2, '2015-11-18', 'Doesn\'t Toast Evenly I have now gone through 3 Cuisinart toasters that don\'t toast anywhere close to evenly on both sides.  Why is it so hard to make a toaster that can do something so basic?'),
(5565, 7, 3, 4, '2015-08-19', 'I love the flexibility of this coffee maker, brews great mug faster than Keurig and you can use ground coffee BUT I find that the standard coffee pods do not fit only the smaller pods with mesh containers work, that\'s ok I can buy that kind but it seems odd even the samples they included are too big for this machine ??'),
(5566, 5, 1, 4, '2014-08-04', 'Excellent An excellent coffee maker.'),
(5567, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'Easy Coffee Making So easy to use and makes great coffee.'),
(5568, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-24', 'Five Stars Cooks everything quick and perfectly'),
(5569, 12, 1, 4, '2016-03-30', 'Four Stars great'),
(5570, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'This is perfect for heating/reheating small dinners This is perfect for heating/reheating small dinners.  It uses very little electricity and takes only minutes.  I don\'t use it for toasting- haven\'t tried that feature.'),
(5571, 12, 1, 4, '2014-10-29', 'Four Stars Like having pop up toaster.'),
(5572, 4, 1, 3, '2016-02-22', 'Element is poor. Split open! I loved this toaster when we got it about two years ago. It seemed ok. Toast a little too toast for the settings. But then the element split. It\'s crazy. It shouldn\'t do this. I wasn\'t going to post but after the similar reviews I had too. They have to recall this oven. It is not safe!! Most likely your element will split in due time.'),
(5573, 7, 3, 5, '2014-07-12', 'I have been using this coffee maker for a few months now and I love it! No more heating up old coffee I always get a fresh cup. I really like how hot the coffee brews. You must read the directions to operate the product correctly. You must pour the water in slowly. Others have written that theirs leaks and that\'s not the case they most likely poured the water to fast and it overflowed on the counter. Read the directions and you will have no problem. I have bought several now for all of my family members and they to love it!'),
(5574, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-01', 'I love this toaster I love this toaster. It\'s just the right size and works great! I liked the one we had at the office and that\'s why I got myself the very same one. Easy to clean. Beeps when done toasting, so you don\'t burn your toast!'),
(5575, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-01', 'Five Stars Love it!!! Size is perfect for one person and really easy to clean.'),
(5576, 5, 1, 4, '2015-04-25', 'Four Stars pleased with this'),
(5577, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-21', 'Five Stars Love this blender'),
(5578, 2, 1, 2, '2016-07-14', 'Two Stars Worked great until the bottom bulb burnt out. Only had it for 10 months.'),
(5579, 4, 1, 2, '2017-01-24', 'Safety warning - faulty heating elements on multiple units!  Watch out! You need to avoid this one, guys - they are built with faulty front elements.  I thought I was alone in this, but a quick internet search shows this is a continual problem with this unit.  After a couple of years of use, our front element actually warped and appears to have melted a bit - it drooped down until it was physically touching the bottom (crumb tray) of the unit.  I\'ve never seen or heard of anything like this with an element in an appliance before.  Two stars instead of one because it did function okay until the meltdown happened, but still...that\'s a major safety issue (faulty elements???  Stay the heck away), and it\'s not worth it when you can find similar units out there for about the same price - there\'s nothing about this one that\'s so amazing that you can\'t find a similar model from another manufacturer.'),
(5580, 6, 1, 1, '2016-04-29', 'Don\'t waste your money Beware! A total waste of money. A name brand on a piece of junk.All features do the same thing even though they claim to defrost, warm etc. Its just on or off. Plus the filaments are spotty and it toasts totally unevenly. Front side of toast pale, back side blackened. English muffin crispy on top edge and uncooked on other edge of same side. Tried to return but missed the cut off date by one day. Garbage!'),
(5581, 5, 1, 1, '2015-04-04', 'One Star This was a great coffeemaker for four months, then this morning it won\'t power on any longer.'),
(5582, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-27', 'Fabulous Find! I was looking for an easy to read water filler. Fabulous! I like that the water container can be lifted from the back to be filled or remain attached... SO EASY TO CLEAN...I also like the swivel out arm to scoop in the coffee. I find I make less spills and if I do spill, it just lands on the counter, not all over the coffee maker. I like the size of the pot and the easy to pour spout- hardly any dripping. I also like that it is easy to program. I like the price!'),
(5583, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'A great price for a great product I REPLACED A MUCH BIGGER AND MORE EXPENSIVE COVECTION OVEN/TOASTER MACHINE, WITH WHICH I WAS NOT PARTICULARLY HAPPY, WITH THIS BLACK & DECKER TOASTER OVEN. I LOVE THIS LITTLE NUMBER- IT DOES ALL IT IS SUPOSSED TO WELL AND EFFICIENTLY. I WOULD BUY IT AGAIN.'),
(5584, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-13', 'Highly recommend This is the best toaster oven I have had in years. I would recommend it to anyone.'),
(5585, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-16', 'Five Stars Love this coffee maker so much I bought a second one for our houseboat.'),
(5586, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-07', 'Momma is happy, so everyone is happy I bought one of these for my 85-year-old mom because her old one was filthy.  She has simple cooking habits nowadays and hasn\'t complained about it.  Momma is happy, so everyone is happy.'),
(5587, 2, 1, 4, '2016-09-05', 'Four Stars There\'s no bagel option. WHAT IF I ONLY WANT ONE SIDE TOASTED, YOU MONSTERS?!.'),
(5588, 6, 1, 3, '2015-07-03', 'It fails to toast evenly just like every other toaster in this price range It fails to toast evenly just like every other toaster in this price range. It gets the job done for a pretty reasonable price though.'),
(5589, 8, 1, 3, '2016-09-29', 'Three Stars The disc freezes in the middle, a bit.'),
(5590, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'GREAT PRODUCT EASY TO USE,,,LOTS OF CUP SIZE AND TYPES OF DRINKS TO CHOOSE FROM,, ONLY NEGATIVE THING IS THAT IT IS A BIT NOISY-- WHEN COFFEE/DRINK IS BEING DISPERSED, OTHER THAN THAT-- I WOULD BUY AGAIN,,, THANKS KEURIG FRO THE FREE PODS FOR THIS REVIEW...'),
(5591, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'Excellent value. Brews great coffee. Love the convenience features and ease of use.'),
(5592, 2, 1, 3, '2016-09-17', 'Confusing directions but works great While it works great the directions are super confusing at first. I have to turn three knobs to cook toast. Works great tho.'),
(5593, 5, 1, 4, '2016-04-11', 'love this machine! after years of great service, my old black and decker coffee pot finally died. went and bought another one locally and it lasted 3 months before clock decided to lose a hour everyday, and the warming plate rusted. frustarted, i came online and looked on here for a replacement, and i wasn\'t going to buy another black and decker. this coffeemaker is very reasonable in price, and has TONS of features. here are the pros: 1. removable water tank. this is very nice, you simply take off the tank and fill in sink. in my case, i use filtered water, so i take to the fridge and fill with filtered cold water. a great feature, and its very easy to clean, and you can just toss in sink once a week to clean. 2. filter basket- on the side of the machine, there is a button, push it and the filter basket swings out for easy filling with coffee and or filters. you can use the permanent filter (not included) but i have elected to use the non bleached brown paper filters. no issues with overflow, etc. filter basket has a spring valve on bottom so when you remove carafe to sneak a cup during brewing, coffee doesn\'t drip on the warming plate and cause it to rust. this was a issue with other machines i have owned. 3. carafe is easy to hold in your hand, and feels solid. the design of the carafe allows you to pour a cup without getting coffee everywhere. a very good feature! 4. nice bright lcd screen-screen is bright and programming is super easy. you can even adjust the warming plate temprature. so your coffee doesn\'t have that burnt taste after brewing. i keep the setting on medium, and have had no issues. 5. small vent on top for steam to vent- nice small opening for steam to vent when coffee is brewing. i have noticed other reviews that say the faceplate around the controls comes off suddenly. i have had this machine a week and i see no signs of the faceplate becoming loose, etc. as of this writing, i can\'t say i find any cons with this machine. it just works and does a great job. if you are tired of other machines and there quirks, pick this one up today. it\'s a great buy.'),
(5594, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-09', 'Works like a charm - compact Works like a charm - compact, good directions and a needed addition to my kitchenette counter. My only negative comment would be the small lettering and numerals...getting used to that as well. Sister Irene Duchesneau'),
(5595, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-09', 'Good fairly compact in size Good fairly compact in size. This a great sized toaster oven that doesn\'t take up too much space. It can fit up to 6 pieces of English Muffins. The \"done\" beeper is rather loud and startled us but once you get used to it, you appreciate it.'),
(5596, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-15', 'This is the best Toaster Oven I have ever owned This is the best Toaster Oven I have ever owned. The oven getting REALLY hot and fast. The toaster part of the oven ACTUALLY toast instead of making warm bread. Beware: TOASTER does not have a timer lso be sure to pay CLOSE ATTENTION! : )'),
(5597, 8, 1, 3, '2014-11-08', 'It makes a good \'luke warm\' cup of coffee I bought mine at Kroger. It\'s cheap, it works. But, the problem I have is the heat level. It makes a good \'luke warm\' cup of coffee. When I pour a fresh cup I have to put it in the microwave to get it good and hot. I guess it\'s a liability issue; you know, like that idiot who scalded her crotch and sued McDonalds to pay for her stupidity.'),
(5598, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'Perfect This toaster oven is the perfect combination of oven and toaster. It\'s great!'),
(5599, 10, 1, 4, '2016-01-10', 'Like this blender Like this blender. It\'s so adorable, affordable and cute. It\'s small and great for traveling. Simple to use and because it\'s so small, easy to keep in your kitchen.'),
(5600, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Great brewer I love this machine.  It\'s quick and easy to use.  I get a perfect cup of coffee every time and cleaning is simple.  Thanks Keurig for another great product. And Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(5601, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-29', 'Can handle green smoothies - just don\'t use kale This blender, of course, isn\'t going to be as powerful as the bigger, more expensive blenders but for the price it\'s great.  The small size makes it easy to clean and carry and being able to drink directly from the blender cuts down on dishes. Also, I\'ve found that it\'s more than powerful enough to incorporate frozen bananas and frozen berries into my smoothies. It can even handle green smoothies for the most part. It can\'t really handle kale, though -- in the first picture I\'ve uploaded (the one without the lid) you can see that the kale still remained in little flakes that were somewhat off-putting. They were too  small to taste, but they definitely messed with the texture. In the second picture I used spinach instead and you can see that there are no flakes (the tiny dark spots are bubbles), just a smooth, thick smoothie.'),
(5602, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-09', 'Four Stars it is very useful'),
(5603, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-12', 'Easy to use and makes great coffee. Love this coffee maker.  We make the coffee strong and it tastes like espresso that we love.'),
(5604, 6, 1, 3, '2015-09-06', 'Otherwise it\'s fine. With a \"bagel\" setting, I was expecting a wider mouth to accept a split bagel. Otherwise it\'s fine.'),
(5605, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-08', 'Five Stars Great toaster, finally one toasts evenly every time. Well worth the money.'),
(5606, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-16', 'Four Stars I love it'),
(5607, 6, 1, 3, '2017-01-06', '4 slicer becomes 2 slicer Well after about a year this thing turned into a 2 slice toaster! one side of the heating coils went out!! Oh well !.'),
(5608, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-04', 'Nice simple and small appliance. We needed to replace/upgrade our old toaster oven.  The problem we found was that most newer ones took up too much counter space and were complicated to use.  This one is perfect!  Small, yet large enough to fit several items in there at one time, easy to use and it\'s appearance is plain and simple.  I will say this, the only thing we have had to get used to is the timer alarm - it sounds like our smoke alarm - louder than I would like, but OK.'),
(5609, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-15', 'Does what it\'s supposed to do Great little blender'),
(5610, 6, 1, 4, '2014-06-08', 'It Was a Gift Since I bought the toaster for my niece as a gift I can only go by what she\'s told me -- that she likes it.  Nothing special, it just does the job it was made to do.'),
(5611, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Five Stars Sleek looking and easy to use. Makes excellent coffee.'),
(5612, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Keurig works for me loving this! wasn\'t sure it would work for me, but I\'m really glad I have one...coffee is great, and no wasted brew if I decide I don\'t want a second cup.Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5613, 6, 1, 4, '2014-11-04', 'Does the trick at a good price. they don\'t last forever but this is ... Does the trick at a good price.they don\'t last forever but this is my 2nd.'),
(5614, 2, 1, 4, '2015-04-20', 'Four Stars So far, so good'),
(5615, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-01', 'Five Stars it works fine, suit my needs'),
(5616, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-14', 'Five Stars Great...'),
(5617, 2, 1, 1, '2016-01-11', 'Broken Does not work at all!'),
(5618, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-22', 'good product. Hard to get the proper setting between ... Works well, good product. Hard to get the proper setting between burn and toast.'),
(5619, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-19', 'A great coffee maker for a reasonable price. Very nice compact unit.  The water container is easy to remove and carry to the sink for filling.  Really like the swing-out coffee ground holder rather than a lift-up top as it fits under my kitchen cabinet very nicely.  The carafe really is non-drip.  Timer works well so you can have your first cup of coffee upon awakening!  So far, no problems at all and hope that it will last for a good long while!'),
(5620, 11, 1, 3, '2015-03-08', 'Good toaster.....but.... This toaster we received as wedding gift.  The toaster itself works great and we can\'t really complain on it\'s performance as a toaster.  The reason for the 3 star review is because the timer element of this toaster stopped working after week.  This is an inconvenience for us and I would not recommend buying it again.'),
(5621, 7, 3, 4, '2016-12-21', 'I can make a quick cup of coffee to take on the road with me to walk or shop. So easy to prepare and simple to keep clean. I recommend this Coffee Maker for the person on the go.'),
(5622, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'I love my Keurig I love my Keurig. It is wonderful and convenient. Just as simple as refilling some water, not only does it get filtered but in seconds I have a nice cup of tea or hot chocolate. I can\'t wait to purchase more for my Keurig. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5623, 6, 1, 1, '2015-03-30', 'Think twice on this product I had hoped ordering a Cuisinart product that it would function as advertised. This toaster does not even come close to functioning as advertised. Every time I put in a piece of bread it comes out light brown on one side and literally burnt black on the other. What a waste of money, and the costs and hassle of return make it a waste of time.'),
(5624, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-06', 'Five Stars we\'ve been using it for at least a year, works well.'),
(5625, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'Makes great toast This is so much better than a $10 basic toaster. It makes great toast and is simple to use.'),
(5626, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-27', 'Space Saving 2.0 My new Keurig 2.0 Brewer is Great. I have limited counter space, it fits perfectly. It brews quickly, I have fresh brewed ice tea everyday. Thank you Keurig for the free pods upon completion of this review.'),
(5627, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-27', 'Four Stars Great coffee and easy set-up and instructions for brewing.'),
(5628, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-25', 'Five Stars Works great!'),
(5629, 3, 1, 1, '2016-09-20', 'Display ISN\'T backlit like shown on the website photo Display ISN\'T backlit like shown on the website photo. The display is hard to read, as are the push-buttons. The oven door, once started to open, falls down without any resistance as if a return spring was missing. Tried heating pre-cooked frozen enchiladas twice. Typically they bake at 350 for 45 minutes in a regular oven, and in my last Breville. I baked them without the convection fan running ... which the book says when used, you should decrease the temp by 25. Well both times, the enchiladas came out still cold in the middle of their length. It\'s going back.'),
(5630, 11, 1, 1, '2014-08-11', 'HOT to the touch and confusing settings This is NOT a good toaster. it gets HOT to the touch and with a 3 year old in the house that can get grabby, that\'s not a good thing. The handle on the door was so hot I had to use oven mitts to open it while toasting bread. I am afraid to have anything near it. My poptart caught on fire this morning as well and I made sure to have the timer on and the setting to \"toast lightly\" so I assumed that would mean simply crisping up the outside & getting the inside melty. Apparently not. I also do not like the \"stay on\" feature. It is in an odd location since it\'s at the end of the dial where OFF should be. Seems like another fire hazard waiting to happen. We will be returning this toaster.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(5631, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-31', 'Good Unit A great unit. Looks good. Quality material. All that we expected for the price'),
(5632, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-24', 'We love this coffee pot We love this coffee pot. The coffee is hot and flavorful, the design is sleek and interesting, and there is no carafe to break.'),
(5633, 9, 1, 2, '2016-09-27', '... coffee would drip out of bottom never had very good luck with cuisinart coffee makers wouldn\'t buy any of ... No along lasting product didn\'t even have it for a year and coffee would drip out of bottom never had very good luck with cuisinart coffee makers wouldn\'t buy any of their products again.'),
(5634, 11, 1, 1, '2014-08-06', 'Oven showed up with only the shell. No shelves ... Oven showed up with only the shell. No shelves, etc. Such a pain in the butt. Seriously, how does a toaster oven come with no shelves? This was a birthday gift for my mother in law and now it\'s a huge FLOP!'),
(5635, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-14', 'Five Stars Excellent toaster oven.  Attractive too.'),
(5636, 5, 1, 4, '2015-04-24', 'Good basic coffeemaker I wanted a basic coffeemaker and purchased this one after my old Cuisinart one broke. Pros: great for under cabinets - the basket opens with a click of a button. The water reservoir can be taken out and filled. Love the \"strong\" brew option, you can either make stronger coffee, or use less coffee. Cons: does not keep coffee hot for a long time! It has 3 settings, and the longest is about 1 hour. That\'s the biggest disappointment for me, because I used to make lots of coffee with my Cuisinart coffeemaker, and keep it hot for 4 hours, and it still tasted great.'),
(5637, 1, 1, 3, '2015-10-30', 'K200 - coffee still tastes great I was really excited to purchase the new k200 system. I had an older model and experienced \"short cups\". I was excited to have 9 sizes to choose from. To my disappointment, I can\'t select anything more than a 10 oz cu when using a k cup. A little surprised that my older model had an auto shutoff and this one does not. One would think that would be a standard feature. The coffee still tastes great and the convenience of one cup is worth it! Thanks,Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(5638, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-20', 'Delighted beyond words Exactly what I was looking for at a reasonable prce'),
(5639, 9, 1, 3, '2015-05-19', 'I still love this tho I can\'t fit my cup underneath the spout without pulling out the drip tray. I use a cup similar to a Dunkin Donuts medium size take-out cup. But otherwise it brews great tasting HOT coffee.'),
(5640, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-05', 'LOVE IT The clock is very read-able.  Great feature.  If i slept in the kitchen that may be an issue...but I don\'t. Easy to re-set the time, like if the power goes out. Delay timer works perfectly. Durable pot so far.  I appreciate the filter basket swings out, instead of UP.  I don\'t often remove the back water container, but it is a nice feature to just wash it every now and then.  I set mine on the 1-4 cups mode because I\'m usually only making 2 cups for me. The steam-release at the top is fine, I don\'t have mine under any cabinets anyway, but that\'s how I think all coffee makers are. I really like it.'),
(5641, 2, 1, 2, '2016-07-02', 'dimensions are not as listed which I am finding is ... dimensions are not as listed which I am finding is a most regular occurrence for Amazon. Does anyone really look at the products they sell here?'),
(5642, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-06', 'I debated getting this coffee maker after reading the reviews. So many people reported problems and issues. I have to say my experience has been nothing but positive. If you follow the simple start up instructions you will have great results. This is perfect for my office, I have it on the credenza and it means I don\'t have to get up to get a cup of coffee when I want one and if all I want is one cup a day then I don\'t have to brew a whole pot. I would recommend this to anyone, including just for personal home use. I am going to get another for home because this is so great!'),
(5643, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Love our Keurig We love our Keurig, it is the top of the line and we use it several times a day. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(5644, 10, 1, 3, '2015-01-03', 'The kids like it because easy to clean Gave this to my college age children for Christmas, for on the go smoothies. Works ok, but have to continually shake to get mixture to mix and emulsify evenly. The kids like it because easy to clean, and you can make a smoothie and run out the door with the easy carry cup and lid.'),
