(5676, 4, 1, 2, '2015-05-13', 'Stuck and Shattered I purchased this toaster oven back in December 2013, at the beginning of this year the door started to hang and continued to get harder and harder to open.  Last night door was really stuck and as my husband pulled, the glass shattered and handle broke off.  Was never overly impressed with toasting results but very unhappy it only lasted 2 years before having issues.'),
(5677, 4, 1, 5, '2016-03-09', 'Five Stars I love it.'),
(5678, 8, 1, 5, '2014-03-12', 'Love my Black & Decker coffeemaker! These smaller coffee makers at a reasonable price are hard to find. This one is perfect for me. Thank you.'),
(5679, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-24', 'Five Stars love this coffee pot try and find better for the price you wont'),
(5680, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-02', 'What is nice is the water reservoir comes off for easy cleaning One month with it so far and all is well. What is nice is the water reservoir comes off for easy cleaning, but more importantly, drying out. Price seems reasonable for the quality.'),
(5681, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-19', 'Wish we had a new personal blender that was sturdy This blender was rated very high by Consumer Reports.  Ours worked just fine for two weeks--and then it broke.  Amazon gave us a refund, fortunately.  I\'d like to buy another Hamilton Beach personal blender, as we liked the blender.  However,  I\'m not sure the hassle of having to return another broken one would be worth it.'),
(5682, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-14', 'THE BEST EVER We love this Coffee maker. This is my 3rd one. LOL. I know that sounds bad but my husband drinks 3 to 4 pots a day so it gets a work out so I replace it every year. I love that the back come off to fill with water. We had the ones you have to use the pot to fill it but it gets very unsanitary even if you use the cleaner so I wanted the detachable water reservoir. Love it.'),
(5683, 7, 3, 5, '2015-10-09', 'I got this for my grandson to put in his dorm room because they cannot have hot plates. He absolutely loves it!'),
(5684, 1, 1, 2, '2016-05-10', 'This K250 does not compare well to previous generation. ... This K250 does not compare well to previous generation.  I get coffee grounds in every cup and the brewer spits out the water/coffee, splattering on the counter every time.'),
(5685, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-15', 'Five Stars Excellent product.'),
(5686, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'Five Stars A good looking, user friendly product and it works great!'),
(5687, 2, 1, 1, '2016-01-05', 'Malfunctioned - handle melted Pass on this model and save yourself the trouble of a return. The handle melted and fell off this oven the first time I used the bake feature. It is not well made. I\'ve had another B&D oven that worked fine for many years. They\'ve cut corners on this model and it shows.'),
(5688, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-20', 'They really love this toaster oven and it save energy and lowers ... Was a for relative. They really love this toaster oven and it save energy and lowers her electric bill!'),
(5689, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-22', 'Fire Fire Fire Don\'t put taco shells in there or they\'ll burst into flames within a minute.'),
(5690, 9, 1, 1, '2016-02-08', 'I had one in 2012 and it started leaking coffee ... I had one in 2012 and it started leaking coffee after one year.  Cuisinart reluctantly replaced it and now the new one is doing the exact same thing.  It\'s a defect in this model and although I contacted Cuisinart, they didn\'t seem to be concerned.  I would not buy another Cuisinart since they don\'t stand behind their products.'),
(5691, 12, 1, 5, '2015-11-08', 'Five Stars Love this toaster'),
(5692, 10, 1, 4, '2015-07-25', 'Definitely good product for the money What you see is what you get. Definitely good product for the money. The only con is I can\'t seem to find an extra cup/container so I can have an extra while the other one is dirty.'),
(5693, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-05', 'Great product. It allows me to brew k-cups along with ground coffee. No matter whom I am brewing coffee for I am able to make the perfect cup for family and friends.'),
(5694, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-30', 'Five Stars love it.'),
(5695, 3, 1, 3, '2014-06-02', 'Geezer alert! If you\'re over 50, make sure you order a spare set of readers to keep near this thing.  It\'s a nice oven, but the controls are not intuitive by any means and are very difficult to read.'),
(5696, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-11', 'So far so good, I hope my coffee maker lasts longer then ... So far so good, I hope my coffee maker lasts longer then ones of reviews I\'ve read. Have had two Cuisiarts which lasted about 2 years each and cost a fortune. This cost half the price, makes good coffee and keeps it hot. The only problem is that I do not program, so it blinks constantly which is a pain...probably make it fail faster, but I never keep small appliances plugged it so it would need reprograming every day anyhow.'),
(5697, 8, 1, 5, '2014-01-19', 'Perfect Size for little cabin We have a very small cabin and this was the perfect size to fit in my kitchen. It makes a great cup of coffee!!'),
(5698, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-04', 'One Star Tried to use this to make bullet proof coffee, but leaked everywhere. Will be returning and buying another blender.'),
(5699, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-01', '<3 <3 This Keurig is amazing for the price! Being the only person in my household that drinks coffee, it is very nice to be able to brew just one cup at a time. The carafe option is nice to have, though I have not used it yet. I also have the My Kcup so that I can brew my own coffee (much cheaper than buying all those little cups) and it works very nicely. Love the color, too! ;)'),
(5700, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-09', 'Best toaster I have ever tried! This toaster is amazing not only for the price but just a great toaster in general! When you push the toast down it takes it and grabs it down, no pushing several times to make it stay!! Just one push and it\'s down! Then when the toast pops up you can lift the tab up and it elevates the toast quite nicely with ample space for your fingers. Aaaaand toasts the toast evenly on each side. It has a defrost option which is great. As an added bonus, it has a blue light to notify you when it is toasting. So happy with my purchase!! Would totally buy it again!'),
(5701, 11, 1, 1, '2014-10-09', 'One Star It is too small and temperature does not remain stable.'),
(5702, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-21', 'If this is the type of coffee maker that you have used you won\'t be disappointed. I have bought Cuisinart appliances for years due to outstanding warranty, and product.  I was waiting for my previous version to die before I bought this one but decided after three years to go ahead and purchase (I donated the old one).  If this is the type of coffee maker that you have used you won\'t be disappointed.'),
(5703, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-31', 'Five Stars VERY NICE NO BURNT TOAST ANYMORE SETTINGS ARE PERFECT'),
(5704, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Great quality I love this new coffee maker we had a Hamilton one that did not have a pot and it always leaked after about nine months, the convenience of no pot, I bought three of them and they were around $65.00 this Cuisinart is so much better quality!'),
(5705, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-14', 'It practically blew up Basically you are paying for what you get. Used it maybe 5 or more times. It started to make a fiery smoke smell and stopped working. My friend encountered the same issue. Don\'t buy something more expensive that can actually blend ice is a way better option.'),
(5706, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-31', 'Wish I Could Mix Old and New Together The pros: I really love the color of this brewer and it\'s a great addition to my kitchen. I love the touch display aspect and that there\'s a hot water function. I also like there\'s a function to make the coffee strong. The qualms I have with the 2.0 brewer is that (1) the water filter can be a little bit tricky to put on especially when it\'s full of water - I\'ve spilled a couple times but this could be because I need to get use to the new configuration; (2) not all K-cups work in the brewer that should (Meza coffee brand for one); and (3) there isn\'t a reusable pod for it at this moment I\'m writing this review so you have to buy pods. I originally was going to keep this brewer at home but I\'ve decided to take it in the office instead. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5707, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-01', 'BACK TO THE FUTURE I had to buy a new toaster oven when my 10 year old B&D died. The previous one also lasted at least 10 years. After reading the reviews I figured I might as well stick with B&D. The look is retro which is nice. Luckily there is an outlet right behind this appliance; otherwise the very short cord would have been a major problem. This item does a good job of making toast, English muffins and bagels. It is also good at heating up small things. The thing that drives us crazy is the ticking sound when it is turned on since there is no automatic shut off like my old unit. We are used to it by now but it is still annoying. Since there is no automatic shut off plus an inexact timer, you have to stay by the unit to make sure the toast or whatever does not burn. I used to be able to walk away when making toast knowing it would turn off by itself. So you need to do a bit of experimentation to figure out how far to turn the timer knob. Personally we miss our old unit and don\'t see any improvements in the new one but I guess you have to go with the flow.'),
(5708, 6, 1, 1, '2015-03-11', 'Unhappy Very disaapointed, both slots toast the bread unevenly, one side darker several shades than the other. Seems cheaply made.'),
(5709, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'Five Stars very simple, stylish, & small enough w/ full function for Manhattan Apartment.'),
(5710, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-23', 'Pretty Nice! This brewer is awesome. Easy to use and affordable. Good to have if you  aren\'t a huge coffee fan who drinks like 5 cups in the morning!'),
(5711, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-08', 'Five Stars love it'),
(5712, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-31', 'Very nice Coffee maker!!! Great coffee make being using for awhile haven\'t had any problems out of it works as expected. I really like the detachable water tank on the back works out really great for me!!!'),
(5713, 11, 1, 1, '2015-01-16', 'Crappy Toaster! Makes a mess, and stops toasting well after a couple of months! Horrible horrible toaster! Crumbs constantly fall out of the gap between the bottom of the glass and metal frame of the toaster. It constantly makes a mess! We\'ve had it for 6 months, and the toaster started toasting unevenly and burning half the bread about 2 months ago! I\'m done!!! CRAP! DO NOT BUY!'),
(5714, 9, 1, 4, '2015-04-25', 'Four Stars We like it so far,easy to use and love the coffee on demand feature.  Would recommend it'),
(5715, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Good upgrade Nice unit. Upgraded from the standard old model. Much quicker, better options as far as size of cup. Issue of not recognizing non Keurig cups is not an issue for me, so no biggie. Happy with my purchase. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5716, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Fantastic! I purchased this after using a Mr Coffee for years.  I wanted hotter coffee, no pods & the option to drink a cup on demand as I run a lot of errands and didn\'t want to have to microwave a cold cup.  This works better than I thought.  It keeps my coffee hot for 4 hours with no burning & my coffee tastes better than ever!  Comes with one water filter and I purchased a years supply on Amazon instead of local store & saved $40.  Been using for over a month - no problems - easy to use & clean.'),
(5717, 9, 1, 4, '2016-04-25', 'weak finished alarm. Works great except the finished alarm is so weak that you can not hear it if you are standing next to it.'),
(5718, 8, 1, 1, '2016-09-17', 'It leaks water down the sides every time. I ... It leaks water down the sides every time. I also have to weigh the lid down to slow the leaking.'),
(5719, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-31', 'Its awesome! Perfect size for my small kitchen I recently moved to my own apartment and got as a present the Keurig K250.  Its awesome! Perfect size for my small kitchen! and turquoise color makes everyone notice it and want a cup of coffee :).  I love that it has a touch screen and it has the option for hot chocolate and/or other! The one at my old place didn\'t have that.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5720, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'Five Stars Just what I was looking for.'),
(5721, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-04', 'Five Stars My last Cuisinart toaster lasted over seven years so I decided to get another. Quick delivery.'),
(5722, 12, 1, 5, '2016-03-18', 'Love it. I have bought three of these over the past 25 years and use it every day for toast, pizza, whatever.....Love it.'),
(5723, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Five Stars Use it almost daily!'),
(5724, 10, 1, 1, '2015-08-05', 'Horrible, do not purchase Horrible, do not purchase. I used it only 4 times and the motor burned out. I did not over use it, stuff it packed, leave it running for long periods of time. It started to smoke and it went in the trash.'),
(5725, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-25', 'Great little bleader Great little bleader.  I even take my with me when we go on trips since its small.  Great valve for the money.'),
(5726, 5, 1, 3, '2015-10-17', 'But some of the functions doesnt even make sense like 1-4 cups option it filters 6 cups even if ... Its a basic coffee maker. But some of the functions doesnt even make sense like 1-4 cups option it filters  6 cups even if the option is on'),
(5727, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'we like it. We really like it. We had a little trouble getting the toaster setting right but now we have it and we\'re not burning it anymore. Just had to put it on a very light setting'),
(5728, 12, 1, 2, '2016-11-15', 'Read the reviews carefully to see if it\'s really what you want. I didn\'t like it at all. The toaster doesn\'t toast evenly. The oven burns everything on top. I thought it must be broken, but another reviewer said it was because you need to put something on top of the toaster slots to insulate it or the oven element will stay on. But that is crazy; the design is terrible. The oven cavity is too small to use for anything. And it doesn\'t have a timer. I sent it back.'),
(5729, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-12', 'buy it now Definitely worth the purchase,  cuz I was sick of microwaves I had to find an alternative so I came across this with that price, I was like it wont hurt to try. Then when I got it and try it I was so happy I ddon\'t have to use microwave anymore. It heats up anything pretty fast. And I actually made burgers and hotdogs with it. So its like an oven But faster cuz the heat coil is close to the tray.  The only minus that its a little small like it wont fit a wide plate. Microwaves are bad for you cuz they eat your food before you do. Best alternative.'),
(5730, 6, 1, 2, '2016-11-02', 'UNeven Toasting Uneven toasting. One side is ALWAYS browner than the other.'),
(5731, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Very Happy with purchase! Recently purchased this brewer and am most happy with it. Very pleasing look and most convenient way to brew coffee I have ever experienced. Would definitely reccomend to others.Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5732, 9, 1, 4, '2015-09-14', 'Brews good coffee. I like that it has no carafe Brews good coffee. I like that it has no carafe. Keeps the coffee warm for a couple hours without burning it. I have read complaints about gauge, but it seems pretty accurate in my experience.'),
(5733, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-12', 'Great Product Works well - simple controls and accurate heating.'),
(5734, 11, 1, 4, '2014-11-01', 'but it would be helpful to have better guidelines for toast - we even seem to burn ... use it every day, but it would be helpful to have better guidelines for toast - we even seem to burn it or it is underdone!'),
(5735, 6, 1, 3, '2014-02-23', 'You can do better if you want to spend more money. the toaster doesn\'t do the sides evenly, but it\'s not so bad that I returned the item. It is the right size for my kitchen, and it isn\'t used every day. If I had to do toast every day for a family I wouldn\'t buy it.'),
(5736, 9, 1, 1, '2016-06-26', 'Bad buy Plastic coffee not hot'),
(5737, 9, 1, 2, '2016-10-15', 'very short cord...too short purchased based on popular consumer magazine\'s review. opened to find a VERY short cord, supposedly to avoid tangling. WOW, never had that problem with any of the other 10 different coffee makers. In order to have programmed delivery of coffee, you have to pull out the unit which unplugs it. Hard to know what Cuisinart was thinking. I am NOT thrilled with this. Directions recommend using an extension cord. How does that protect from cord tangling.'),
(5738, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-30', 'My new best friend in the kitchen I bought this a few months ago and wanted to wait to write a review...I absolutely love this toaster oven! I do so much more than make toast with it...I\'ve cooked pizzas, lasagna, loaf breads, cookies, etc. It\'s totally worth reading the booklet that comes with it to learn all of the functions. I can\'t tell you the last time I turned on my oven as this little beauty does it all!.'),
(5739, 7, 3, 1, '2014-02-21', 'I really wanted it to work, I thought it was a great idea. The coffee always comes out so weak. You can only put as much ground coffee to not go over the line and that is just too little grounds. The k-cups just don.t work. The coffee I get from them is just so so weak. The pods which they claim works in this pot just turns out colored water. Too weak. I am returning mine.'),
(5740, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-10', 'Better than any toaster Replaced my $10 bagel toaster with this, and loving it so far. I only use it for toast, but I know it can be used for lots of other cooking. I can say for toasting, it is perfect and easy to clean.'),
(5741, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'She loved it! It was a gift!  She loved it!'),
(5742, 11, 1, 4, '2014-06-26', 'small size but does a big job This toaster oven works exactly as advertised, is quick acting, and very easy to clean. I didn\'t give it 5 stars because the first time it is was used there waqs a dreadful smell, like a burning chemical. The toaster oven must have been coated with something, but it burned off and is not detected on additional use. It is compact, and looks attractive on my kitchen counter.'),
(5743, 8, 1, 1, '2016-09-12', 'Can\'t believe Amazon is selling products like this. Top lid hinge snapped broken after one use. Can\'t believe Amazon is selling products like this.'),
(5744, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-16', 'Four Stars Very basic, but works as described. Compact size it what I needed for small space at office.'),
(5745, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-24', 'Love this coffee maker. Coffee stays fresh for hours. No bitter taste from sitting on a burner like traditional coffee makers. Works and looks great. So happy we bought this model.'),
(5746, 8, 1, 5, '2014-09-18', 'Five Stars very good'),
(5747, 2, 1, 3, '2015-12-23', 'Not sure if it\'s damaged due to shipping or bad quality check? Sending it back because the glass door has a crack in it. Not sure this glass door is even safe enough to heat up the toaster oven? Don\'t even want to test it and risk it cracking more.'),
(5748, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'HAPPY HAPPY HAPPY!! Its well made tool made by the company it make the lifestyle so easy i am very happy with this'),
(5749, 11, 1, 3, '2014-10-04', 'Three Stars Toaster handle gets extremely hot. That\'s my only negative comment.'),
(5750, 8, 1, 1, '2015-08-06', 'Cheap plastic smell. I had to return it due to terrible cheap plastic smell. I know this coffee maker is cheap but that doesn\'t mean my coffee has to smell like cheap plastic. I don\'t trust this product. After smelling plastic I wonder if this product is even BPA free.'),
(5751, 12, 1, 2, '2014-11-04', 'Beautiful but the oven usually burns the food (the space ... Beautiful but the oven usually burns the food (the space is too small and the burner stays too close of the grill) and there is no timer.'),
(5752, 5, 1, 4, '2014-11-30', 'This coffee maker appears to be a great buy. It works as noted in the description This coffee maker appears to be a great buy.  It works as noted in the description.  The container that holds the water is especially handy and easy to fill.  I am very happy with this purchase so far!'),
(5753, 8, 1, 4, '2016-08-29', 'fairly fast, cheap to use, good value about as fast as using a melitta filter. Coffee is hotter than I expected, which is a plus. Its a little noisy as it approaches the end of the brewing, but not too bad. I love that I can use my own coffee and don\'t have to buy expensive and bad for the environment pods.'),
(5754, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'Five Stars Great for when you don\'t want to use your main oven'),
(5755, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-25', 'Just Ingenious!! I made this purchase the same time along with Fire TV. I am very impressed and pleased with Hamilton Beach products and have had excellent experiences with their products in the past. Well.. it was time to upgrade my old Hamilton Beach coffee maker, ( It still worked just fine) because I was making some changes to my kitchen. I happen to see this model online at Amazon, I read the reviews which were 90% positive sop I decided to purchase this model. Well after a long unnecessary delay by the worst carriers in the nation (USPS) it finally arrived. I couldn\'t be happier, this model is very compact compared to my older model but don\'t let that fool you. Whoever is responsible for designing this model should win a award, its like they were in my head!. Besides being compact and fitting very well with my new dcor making coffee is a breeze. The baskets swings out and then lifts out to clean and add your filter and coffee, no more filling the carafe with water then filling up the coffee maker. The water reservoir in the back slides out so you can fill it up to the desired level and then slides back in place. (Ingenious). Programming is very easy and it makes like my old one the best cup of coffee. I have owned it all of 1 week and I love it, woke up today to the smell of fresh coffee and kept that coffee hot until I tuned it off. The designer MUST have been in my head when he designed this model, I am very pleased and will continue to purchase Hamilton Beach products.'),
(5756, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-25', 'It is black and silver. Top opens nice and easy for water placement. The water reservoir is in the back, and the coffee container is right in front of it. You can either use ground coffee or single serve cups. The water reservoir and the coffee placement compartment are removable so you can easily clean them. First thing I always do with every coffee machine is run water and vinegar in the water compartment to get rid of any metal taste from new machine. Once I did this I started to make the cup of coffee with ground coffee. Brews the coffee very fast and is very easy to use. I used regular setting and the coffee came out delicious. Just right in color and taste. Brewed very fast. You can adjust the cup rest height to the size of your cup. This machine can even hold a tall travel mug 14 oz. or your regular cup 8-12 oz. I\'ve been told that if you use the Bold setting to make coffee, your grounds may backup into the machine and cause problems. I loved the Regular setting coffee it came out great for my taste. I will use this only. One large cup at a time on quick morning or evening or any time of day. For my needs this machine is great and I really like lit. It does not take much room, fits right in on the spot I have for it. Has lights to indicate \"ready\" or low water. Easy to use for sure.'),
(5757, 10, 1, 4, '2016-09-16', 'A bit weak but perfect for after workout smoothies A bit weak but perfect for after workout smoothies.  You get what you pay for.  I\'m still using this two years later but there is a difference between this and a full sized blender.  Good for protein shakes!.'),
(5758, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Excellent toaster Works well and has many options. For the money you can\'t do better. In fact, it is better than the higher priced toasters.'),
(5759, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-04', 'Five Stars Purchased as a Christmas present for the hubby. He absolutely loves it!'),
(5760, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-04', 'A great coffee pot for the money. The unit makes a 12 cup decanter in less than 15 minutes. Ease of use programming, easy basket insert and removal and easy water fill. Thank you.'),
(5761, 5, 1, 2, '2016-09-13', 'The design is not that great. Mine stopped working in 6 months Design is compact and it works. The problem is when the door is slightly opened, steam got inside and it could ruin the unit. The design is not that great. Mine stopped working in 6 months. The service is good. They are sending me a replacement unit at no cost but I have to pay the shipping.'),
(5762, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-08', 'Smart  design all around! The reviews on this had me second guessing my purchase, but I can honestly say they were wrong.  I love this machine! The removable water tank is genius! No more soaking the counter pouring water in. The swing out coffee area is clean and neat. And BEST of all for me, is when the brewing is complete, the machine is silent! No beeps to wake me at 4:30 am when I set the auto brew. Very happy with this purchase for the price.'),
(5763, 8, 1, 4, '2016-09-10', 'It\'s good for the price Tiny coffee maker. It\'s good for the price.'),
(5764, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-20', 'Perfect pot for two Bought this in a bind when traveling.  It was perfect for our morning Joe.  Makes excellent coffee but does NOT turn off automatically, so we\'ve had to be mindful of that.  Sturdy little machine.'),
(5765, 5, 1, 3, '2015-10-15', 'The cutoff valve thing was a problem for me I\'ve had it about two weeks now.  The first week I\'d come downstairs and find coffee all over the counter.  I blamed my family, until one day I pulled the carafe off (at least 30 minutes after it had finished brewing) and coffee started pouring out of the machine!  The little valve with the spring that keeps the coffee in the grounds area and is supposed to close off when the carafe is removed was somehow working in reverse.  It was stopped up  with the carafe on and let fly when the carafe was removed.  After a few days of trying to clean around that little valve thing and thinking that it couldn\'t possibly be doing what it was doing, I pulled hard on that valve/spring gizmo and removed it.  The coffee maker has worked just fine ever since!  I just set the program a little earlier so it would be done before we got up.'),
(5766, 4, 1, 1, '2016-04-08', 'Sadly another review for an exploding door There are already multiple reviews for this toaster oven where the glass door exploded during or after use. Sadly the same thing happened to me after ~9 months of sporadic use. It happened while using the oven feature, a few seconds after I checked on the food and walked away. Could have been much worse had I been holding that door open when it exploded. It\'s under warranty and Cuisinart said they would replace it (no thanks!) but couldn\'t do anything else for me. Fortunately I bought it from BB&B which has a 365 day return policy. Off to try another brand...'),
(5767, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-31', 'good product we have had this for about a month and we are happy with it.some times it doesnt toast evenly on both sides but its ok.'),
(5768, 10, 1, 2, '2016-03-14', 'Breaks easily It blended well, but it broke after two-three weeks. I should have written a review for this way sooner, but it was a huge disappointment. Waste of money.'),
(5769, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-15', 'very poor toasting, burns or under toasted very poor toasting, burns or under toasted, have tried all settings, wife says piece of junk. Need to find A DECENT TOASTER NOW.'),
(5770, 10, 1, 1, '2016-01-20', 'One Star Such a piece of junk.'),
(5771, 4, 1, 2, '2016-08-19', 'BIG Disappointment I purchase this unit in April of 2014 .  I was very reluctant to buy it due to the many bad reviews about the heating element problems. I had assumed (you know what they say about assuming) that Cuisinart would be so concerned and appalled by the element failures that they would obviously have corrected the problem by now (April 2014) Since  I have many Cuisinart appliances including three food processors and like their designs without having a problem, I decided to take a chance. Especially when I compared other toaster ovens. I didn\'t like the prices or the sizes or features of others and the TOB-40 also wouldn\'t look like a monument on my counter top. I bought it and it fit perfectly in my counter space and it cooked and toasted well.  It toasted much faster than my previous units.  The light/dark adjustment could be better but it was fine.  The indicators lines on the knobs were black like the knobs and impossible to see where they were set.  I corrected that with  painting a little Whiteout correction fluid on the lines and could now clearly see where they were set. I was a little aggravated that Cuisinart didn\'t see that. This morning 8/19/16 I went to toast some bread.  I looked in and noticed the top heating elements were BADLY warped and hanging down. One was cracking on the left side (see photo) and the bottom elements were warping in an upward direction. In all of the reviews I read I never read about the top elements failing only the bottom.  If I had a dish in the oven and went to take it out with a oven mitt,the mitt would have no doubt touched the top element and caught fire. I just called Cuisinart and spoke to a pleasant representative. They are sending me a new unit which I had to pay $10 shipping and they want me to cut off the cord and sent that to their facility in Arizona. Others have written that they had to pay for the return of the WHOLE unit, if I did I would not have agreed to it.  I asked the representative, that given all of the problems, did they finally correct the problem. She said she did not know! Attached is a photo of the damaged heating elements.  .....lets see how long the replacement toaster oven they send me lasts.'),
(5772, 3, 1, 5, '2014-01-12', 'A nice oven, controls take a little time to get used to The oven has a large capacity, has done well cooking a variety of things (only a month\'s use, so far), and is simple to use after getting used to the controls. It has dedicated buttons for things like potatoes, toast, and bagels that save the last setting the next time you use it. If you like darker toast and set the level to 5 (longer cooking time) it will apply that setting on the next use.'),
(5773, 9, 1, 1, '2016-07-25', '2 time failure This is our second coffee maker of this model.  The concept is terrific and it is fine...as long as it works, which isn\'t long. The first one started leaking from the dispenser and not emptying the water tank after about a year.  Descaling made only short-lived minor improvements.  Because we like the style we purchased another about 6 months ago.  It also will not empty the tank and the gauge showing how many cups in the resevoir does not register at all.  In fact, it appears that moisture is inside the gauge housing.  Lot of money wasted.  Will not trust another cuisinart.'),
(5774, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-19', 'This coffee maker is very easy to use This coffee maker is very easy to use. The only drawback is that the coffee has a plastic taste and I\'m not sure if it\'s from the innards or the reservoir. I don\'t notice it so much if I add milk and sugar to my coffee but if I try to skip the milk, plastic is all I can taste.'),
(5775, 5, 1, 2, '2016-05-17', 'Two Stars Low quality. Item returned.'),
(5776, 1, 1, 4, '2016-08-13', 'Works great with K-Cups, had to rig-up a converter to use my favorite coffee pods. So far so good!  Doesn\'t work with San Francisco Bay coffee biodegradable coffee pods.  I cut apart one of the sample pods that came with the coffee maker to leave the cup portion inside the maker, and can now use the San Francisco biodegradable pods.  Would give it 5 stars except they keep changing the design trying to get us to use only K-Cups!.'),
(5777, 5, 1, 3, '2015-08-06', 'While I loved it for the year it worked While I loved it for the year it worked, just shy of 13 months after purchase, it has died.  Simply wont do anything.  Powers on but nothing happens.'),
(5778, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-16', 'Works Great Works great! Great design idea. We like how the rear fill tank can be removed for easy filing.'),
(5779, 6, 1, 1, '2014-06-03', 'Did not work at all, burned toast This toaster did not work at all.  Based on other reviews, maybe I got a bum toaster. Toast: burned one side while the other side didn\'t get toasted at all Bagel: If it was lightly toasted, the bagel was cold. To get the bagel warm, the bagel had to get burned. Frozen Waffle: Did not thaw the waffle. I tried all the settings, buttons, and levels.  Nothing worked.'),
(5780, 12, 1, 5, '2014-07-29', 'Looks like there\'s a newer model Still the only top toaster and oven in one out there...! Looks like there\'s a newer model available'),
(5781, 9, 1, 4, '2016-10-04', 'A decent coffee maker for the price, but don\'t expect it to last more than 3 years. I purchased this item in the summer of 2013, after I saw it at my daughter\'s house. It functioned well for just over 3 years and then the main unit began to leak water from the water tank. At first the leak was small, but within a couple weeks it became so large that I could no longer use the coffee maker, so I discarded it.  I mention this because I will likely purchase a new one from Amazon for $87.71 (The price had been $79.89 just last week) and was considering the purchase of the 3-year warrantee for $7.86; however, because the coffee maker lasted just over 3 years and then was unusable, I suspect that the maximum warrantee period available being 3 years is not a coincidence. It seems that nowadays, nothing lasts more than the term of any available warrantee, regardless of the item. I did like the convenience of dispensing once cup/mug of coffee at a time from the reservoir tank, so I will most likely purchase a new coffee maker and the 3-year warranted, given its low cost. If the new unit lasts less than 3 years, I will use the warrantee to obtain a new coffee maker; if it lasts a bit more than 3 years, then my cost per year for the use of the coffee maker will be about $33.00. Since I would certainly rent the Cuisinart coffee maker for that cost per year, I am satisfied with the likely eventuality that it will become unusable in just over 3 years, as did my last one.'),
(5782, 11, 1, 1, '2015-09-17', 'One Star returned not sturdy'),
(5783, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-25', 'Tasty toast ! This toaster makes nice crispy slices of toast and the bagels setting makes a great bagel. The toaster is easy to clean and doesn\'t take up much counter room.'),
(5784, 5, 1, 2, '2015-12-23', 'Two Stars Died after a month. Was somewhat of a pain to get replaced. Second one also had issues.'),
(5785, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-11', 'Five Stars good'),
(5786, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-15', 'Good buy for a toaster Spent too many years with cheaper ones, and with ancient 1930s style ones that required watching.  I\'ve moved into 21st century. Good buy for a toaster.'),
(5787, 4, 1, 4, '2016-02-10', 'Four Stars So far working great'),
(5788, 4, 1, 2, '2016-08-05', 'Had high hopes - and then they were crushed. I bought this at Best Buy, but wanted to review it here. I had a large frigidaire toaster oven that no longer works, so I went with this less expensive model from a different brand. I was hoping that it would be the cheap solution we were looking for. I quickly ran in to several issues. The wire rack sucks. I don\'t know why it is offset on the sides, but it pulls out when the door opens only if it is in the middle indents. If you move it to the bottom, you lose the auto-slide out (just a bracket with a hook) functionality. Why would anyone want to put the rack at the very bottom? Wont food items cook unevenly? Well, it turns out, to fit anything besides bread or a pizza, you have to move the rack down or you don\'t have clearance. Lame. If you have the wire rack in the middle and want to use the baking sheet that comes with it, the baking sheet doesn\'t fit because of some weird bracket that acts as a stopper to keep the wire rack from coming all the way out. I don\'t know if anyone actually tested this toaster oven before manufacturing it. Oh, and apparently the nonstick coating on the baking sheet is the bad kind of nonstick. No thanks! We will be returning this poorly designed piece of junk. It gets 2 stars because the build quality feels somewhat decent, but still junk-like.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(5789, 8, 1, 2, '2014-03-17', 'avoid this especially if you\'re a lefty Before this, I\'ve used \"Mr. Coffee\" brand coffeemakers around the same size and price range so that\'s what I\'m going to be comparing this to . I liked the look of this one better, and how compact it was so I decided to give it a try.  Most of the small appliances in my kitchen are Black and Decker so I expected to like this coffee maker just fine but unfortunately it falls short.  First of all, (this is irrelevant to right handed people), but with my Mr. Coffee the On/ Off switch was on the front and so it was more comfortable to flip the switch for a left hander like me, and also the coffee pot would stay put as I pushed the switch  since its braced against the wall it would only require using one hand to push it. But with this Black and Decker, the on/ off switch is on the right hand SIDE so I have to reach around it awkwardly to turn it off, and the coffeemaker always ends up getting slid to the left on the counter-top as I push the switch, if I don\'t use my other hand to hold it steady.  It sounds like a little thing,  but it gets annoying morning after morning. If you\'re a lefty like me you already have enough little annoyances in your life to deal with. Coffee first thing in the morning should not be one of them.  Additionally, the clear window to view how many cups of water you\'ve added on the Black and Decker is only on the right side, not both sides like the Mr. Coffee has.   The next annoying thing about this coffeemaker is the fact that you have to wait till it\'s entirely done making the coffee before you can remove the carafe and pour yourself a cup. My Mr. Coffee on the other hand was self sealing, it would plug itself automatically and stop dripping when the carafe was removed, (but still keep working), so that you didn\'t have to wait for all the water to filter through before quickly pouring yourself a cup. So unless you wait for the last drop to filter through this black and decker coffeemaker, you\'re going to have some drips. Probably a lot of drips.  and because of those drips ending up on the hot plate that the carafe sits on, keeping it WET, the black coating on the hot plate is peeling off.  I\'ve only had mine for a few months now and a lot of the black coating has already come off.  That NEVER happened with my mr. coffee. (probably because my mr. coffee didnt drip all over the place!)  And usually now  there are coffee stains on my counter to wipe up as well.  Other than that, it makes coffee just fine.  But, you can probably tell by now which brand I\'d recommend instead.'),
(5790, 4, 1, 1, '2015-04-30', 'Fire Hazard Warning! Almost set my kitchen on fire. This product is a Fire Hazard!!! About an hour ago I thought it felt warm in my kitchen so I looked at the stove and it wasn\'t left on from cooking dinner. The microwave hadn\'t been used all day and looked fine, and a quick glance at my cuisinart toaster oven which hadn\'t been used since breakfast 12 hours ago didn\'t have its indicator light on, but even so I passed my hand over it and had figured my father had toasted something for dessert because there was a tiny bit of heat coming off the toaster oven. I double checked that it wasn\'t set to bake or broil and went to go watch some TV. 30 minutes later I begin smelling something hot. Very hot! Ran into the kitchen and this damn toaster oven is running full-bore with the coils glowing bright orange!!! The indicator light was OFF, the top dial was set to toast, middle knob at 150\'f, and the bottom knob at \"medium\" toast darkness. I hit the start/stop button and the power light TURNS ON!! Crap, now where\'s a Catholic priest when I need one! And since Leslie Neilson is dead, I took the easy route and unplugged it. It\'s currently sitting on my garage floor with a fan blowing on it so it will be cool enough to inspect before I go to sleep. I plan on contacting the manufacturer tomorrow to see what their reaction is to what happened. Because had I been out of the house or asleep, this could have burned my house to the ground.'),
(5791, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-03', 'Toaster Oven Love this toaster oven. Easy to use. Doesnt take up too much counter space.'),
(5792, 11, 1, 5, '2014-11-17', 'Five Stars this replaced a bigger unit that broke after 4 years of use, it does the job well'),
(5793, 3, 1, 4, '2014-07-31', 'So far so good So far I\'d say that, for the price, I\'m pleased with this toaster oven.  Does a good job with toast and bagels, reheating leftovers, cooking some frozen foods that taste better from the oven than the microwave.  Fairly simple controls, although it does pay to spend a few minutes with the instructions.  I like how you can adjust the cooking rack to several different heights.  Things I don\'t like:  the top gets VERY hot, something I\'ve never experienced with the two other toaster ovens we\'ve owned.  And the oven door has no \"spring\" to control it, if you open it and let it go it will just plunk down on your counter. Also our past ovens would shut off automatically when the door was opened, this one does not. The ultimate test will be how it holds up over the long run. Less than one month into its life at the time this review was written. So far so good.'),
(5794, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'Five Stars Works great!'),
(5795, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-07', 'Good Ole B&D Toaster It\'s pretty much like any other Black and Decker toaster I\'ve ever used. It heats up pretty well, not quite as evenly as advertised but I\'ve never had one that did so, there\'s that. The controls are a little bit confusing and if it\'s not set quite right you think you turned it on and it doesn\'t heat up. It\'s fine for me because I read the instruction manual but we bought this for our office and some people are confused on how to use it versus the older style that only had two dials and always turned on when you turned the toast dial. Overall it works well meets my expectations of a toaster in this price range.'),
(5796, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-25', 'Handsome and functional Handsome and fully functional, exactly as advertised.'),
(5797, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-04', 'One Star heating rod went out in less than a year, had to replace'),
(5798, 4, 1, 1, '2016-07-29', 'Worked less than one time I tried to use the Cuisinart TOB-40 to toast a pair of English muffins. The operation was easy: set the Function dial to Toast; set the Toast Shade dial to your desired done-ness (I chose medium); press the Start button. It turned on. Great start. After a couple minutes, it shut itself off. When I looked at the English muffins, I did not agree they were toasted to a medium shade, so I closed the door, turned the Toast Shade dial to dark and pressed the start button again. Nothing happened. I figured maybe that was a cool-down safety feature or something (which I also thought would get very annoying - what if you wanted to toast more than one batch of whatever?), so I finished the English muffins in a regular toaster. A day later I tried to turn the toaster oven on again and it wouldn\'t. I tried every setting (toast, bagel, bake, broil) and different outlets (you know, just in case), but it wouldn\'t turn on. I contacted Amazon for a return and they accepted it back with a full refund. I considered getting a replacement instead, but with so many other brands to choose from, I just didn\'t want to give another Cuisinart toaster oven a try.'),
(5799, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-09', 'It works much better than I expected It works much better than I expected. Thanks for this! Thanks for the great reviews.'),
(5800, 6, 1, 5, '2014-08-03', 'We love this toaster We purchased this toaster last year in red at Sur La Table. We love this toaster! It can handle wide/larger pieces of bread. It offers a wide temperature range to toast or reheat bread, pancakes, waffles etc. It has buttons for bagel, defrost, reheat and cancel. Each pair of slots are independent of each other which allows you to toast at different levels for individual preferences. I put frozen bread in the toaster and it does a great job. Nicely toasted and not dried out. My mothers toaster recently went out, so I purchased this one in white on Amazon. The price was excellent compared to what we paid at the specialty store. It is the exact same toaster and performed as well at the one we bought last year. It is easy to empty the two crumb trays and keep it clean. Always does an excellent job toasting and reheating. I have own numerous toasters over the years and this one is exceptional. You will not be disappointed!'),
(5801, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-09', 'Recommend this device Just right size, easy to keep clean.'),
(5802, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-07', 'Five Stars makes great coffee!!'),
(5803, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-12', 'SO FAR BEST COFFEE MAKER THAT I  EVER HAD. I looked at most reviews, and decided on this, and glad I did. I like that the control is on top. The other one I had the controls were on the bottom, and would short out the coffee maker If you spilled water on it as you were filling the reservoir, or if the filter got clogged up which would happen once in a while. If the filter got to wet it would bend over and fall on the coffee grounds which would let the grounds lose and clog the bottom of the basket, then would over flow onto the bottom shorting out the coffee maker. I don\'t have to worry about that with this coffee maker.  What I like is you can fill the reservoir with the coffee pot or just take the reservoir off and fill it. If you still have coffee in the pot, you can get coffee ready for the next day by filling the reservoir, and then fill the basket, so all you have to is wash the pot and hit program and it\'s ready for the next day. The no drip spot seems to work better on this coffee maker then some of the others that I have had in the past.'),
(5804, 6, 1, 3, '2015-02-28', 'Uneven in toasting, but otherwise good characteristics Easy to use, and I like the white color.  However, like every other toaster I\'ve had, it\'s not very even in its toasting.  Sometimes one side is many shades darker than the other.  It\'s nice to have a slot big enough for a bagel, and a bagel-toasting setting too.  Attractive design.'),
(5805, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-23', 'Great coffee machine! Great coffee machine!  I had the previous Cuisinart Coffee-on-Demand model DCC-2000 for 10+ years, the control panel stopped working the other day so I upgraded to the new DCC-3000 model.  I thought 10 years is a pretty good time period for a coffee maker, so why switch brands?  Cuisinart has been a great product for me, so I stuck with them.  So far so good, the new machine is very nice, I love the removable water tank and the auto clean button.  Recommend.'),
(5806, 12, 1, 4, '2014-08-02', 'Winner!! Great Product except for the ridiculously short electric cord that others have noted. Do yourself a favor...order a 1 ft. 16awg extension cord from Amazon at the same time. Toasts very well, oven large enough for open faced sandwiches.  Toasts and Heats quickly.  Winner!'),
(5807, 10, 1, 2, '2016-02-17', 'Two Stars had an american plug on it smelled of smoke when i turned it on'),
(5808, 10, 1, 1, '2016-03-12', 'It\'s good for blending protein powder and almond milk but it ... It\'s good for blending protein powder and almond milk but it can\'t handle adding frozen fruit and ice to your shakes too- mine broke in about 2 wks'),
(5809, 2, 1, 4, '2016-07-06', 'Toaster looks great. Nice size Toaster looks great.  Nice size.  Sleek silver exterior.  $28 price is unbeatable.  Dials are a little bit confusing.  No matter how you set it, it toasts darker than it should. But this problem is easily fixed by standing watch over your toast.'),
(5810, 5, 1, 3, '2016-03-25', 'Meh - another so so coffee pot Try finding a simple, reliable coffee pot that makes a good brew and costs (well, anything). Good luck. This model makes decent coffee, but the Mr. Coffee type brewing basin and filters get less brewed coffee from the beans than a Melita/Braun type cone filter. It groans and snorts throughout its VERY LONG brewing cycle.  The clock, timer and brewing options are easy to set and work well. It looks good. The reservoir is easy to remove, fill, and replace. It doesn\'t leak. The carafe fits very tightly under the springy downspout--so tightly that the first time I set it up I thought it was securely seated when it was not. I walked by and my elbow barely brushed the handle and the carafe leapt to its death on the ceramic tile floor. This is definitely a design problem. The replacement carafes are ridiculously expensive--nearly as much as a new pot with carafe. I settled for this model because of the absence of good, affordable coffee pots. In my office I pulled out a mid-1990s series Braun brewer with cone type filters. It was about $16 new and still makes the best and fastest brew of any electric coffee pot I\'ve encountered. Can\'t find that model now, however.'),
(5811, 10, 1, 3, '2015-12-07', 'Decent price for a decent blender A nice price for a good personal blender. The most annoying thing is that it is NOT dishwasher safe. They def need to update this so it is dishwasher safe. Beyond that...it does the job as intended. It won\'t replace powerful blenders but is nice for single serve drinks. The lid isn\'t the best as it can leak while blending.'),
(5812, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Five Stars Love it and use it almost daily!'),
(5813, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-03', 'Love this coffee maker We\'ve only had this coffee maker a little over two weeks but are very pleased with it.  Our last maker wouldn\'t get the coffee past luke warm so it was time to get a new one.  It\'s very easy to load the water, filter and coffee.  Instructions were easy to understand and the one feature we\'re enjoying is being able to choose our brew strength.  And let me tell you,  we now have HOT coffee.  Stream lined and attractive with easy clean finishes.  Very pleased with all features.'),
(5814, 5, 1, 2, '2014-05-10', 'No quality We needed a replacement coffeemaker after our last Mr Coffee lasted > 5 years without an issue. I liked the removable reservoir and the swing out basket. The 1-4 cup feature sounds nice but we have not tried. On our first use, when removing the reservoir, one of the lid hinge pins snapped off. Now the lid just sits upon the top. And 2 out of the 3 times, the electrical plug comes loose in the socket without anyone being near it, totally loosing power to the machine. You look once, it\'s brewing. You look again a few seconds later, and the machine has powered down. Buy Hamilton Beach breakfast and sandwich makers; buy someone else\'s coffee maker.'),
(5815, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-07', 'Junk Within less than one month, the \'bagel\' function will not stop. I toasted a bagel in it once, and pressed the bagel button. It did what it is supposed to do, that is, the blue light indicator turns on and the bagel is toasted on the cut side (turned toward the center). From that time on, now it will only toast the inside of regular bread, regardless if the bagel button/light is on or off. It\'s ridiculous. This is my second Cuisinart. I used to have the 4-slice for extra long slices of bread. The 4-slice function stopped working after a few years of use, so I gave it away. It was too big anyway, so I bought the compact 2-slice model. This is the last Cuisinart toaster I will ever purchase.'),
(5816, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-04', 'Good in the Kitchen Replaced a toaster with this, use this for toast, heating leftovers, pizza, pretty good product'),
(5817, 9, 1, 2, '2016-12-10', 'Not very happy with this coffee maker Not very happy with this coffee maker.  Looks beautiful but water doesn\'t heat quite as hot as the last Cuisinart coffee maker I had.  Now after just a few months, the coffee just trickles out, the gauge sticks, not the quality I expected.  I may have to return it to Cuisinart.'),
(5818, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-05', 'Five Stars Good size for my counter. Easy to use.toasts evenly and quickly'),
(5819, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-27', 'We love the way it keeps the coffee warm for several ... This is our 3rd Coffee bar.  We love the way it keeps the coffee warm for several hours without making the coffee more bitter.  The design of this version is great - easy to fill the water (vs. an older model we had).  Both or the previous systems we had lasted for several years.  The one thing to remember is that you do have to go to the bar to refill -- but we need the exercise :).'),
(5820, 5, 1, 3, '2016-08-21', 'Three Stars Worked great for about a year then just quit.'),
(5821, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'Five Stars I love it!'),
(5822, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-21', 'Five Stars Really enjoy this toaster... Easy to use gor a variety of breads and bagels... Very fast...'),
(5823, 8, 1, 4, '2014-06-29', 'What a good little coffee maker What a good little coffee maker! For just two people on a daily morning basis, it is perfect. Still going strong after 1 1/2 years. Coffee tastes great and cleanup is easy. Would recommend for one or two people.'),
(5824, 5, 1, 1, '2015-05-17', 'Died after 5 months It worked well to begin with and it has a lot of neat features which is why I bought it. But about 5 months after I bought it...it stopped working. Just dead in the water. Very disappointing.'),
(5825, 5, 1, 2, '2015-10-11', 'Two Stars Great Coffee maker!  But it stopped working after 6 months.'),
(5826, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-02', 'Black & Decker comes through again! An old name in small kitchen appliances still is on top! LOVE the 4 slice capability & simple operation.  Great value for the money!'),
(5827, 9, 1, 3, '2016-02-16', 'Makes good coffee but a little bit of a pain to ... Makes good coffee but a little bit of a pain to clean the coffee well ,and it drips coffee on the counter so you have to keep a napkin under it.'),
(5828, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-05', 'Love this oven it does take up a lot of ... Love this oven it does take up a lot of space but so worth it no more toaster and this will cook so many things!'),
(5829, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-04', 'Can\'t go wrong This coffee makers works great.  It\'s reliable, easy to maintain and just works.  It\'s set every morning to start brewing and it\'s never let us down.  The only thing I would add to it is the ability to dim the LCD display at night as it ends up being an uninvited night light for the kitchen.'),
(5830, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-26', 'Totally dissatisfied! Only toasts one side of bread you have to turn the bread around and toast again.  Sorry I purchased it'),
(5831, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-23', 'Five Stars Perfect!!!.'),
(5832, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-25', 'Great! It\'s a good thing that my wife bought this product. I was able to reheat the foods that she cooks everytime I went home late.'),
(5833, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-21', 'Split Heating Elements Both heating elements have split and begin to arch. Doesn\'t appear to be very safe, and Cuisinart does not supply replacement parts for these elements; they only sell replacement crumb trays and other useless parts. I\'m really upset that I have to go buy yet another toaster oven in just a few short years. I certainly won\'t be buying from Cuisinart this time around...'),
(5834, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-17', 'A+ Coffee Maker Bought as a Christmas gift; an excellent coffee maker. Has a gauge for when coffee supply gets low, but works just fine and makes good coffee, too!!'),
(5835, 4, 1, 5, '2016-12-05', 'Five Stars excellent.'),
(5836, 6, 1, 4, '2016-03-24', 'Nice but NOT compact I got the 4-slice toaster and there\'s nothing compact about it. It\'s large to accommodate four slices of bread. Other than that, it works just fine; we are still trying to get the setting we like just right. The knobs are a bit looser than we prefer so they slide very easily.'),
(5837, 3, 1, 4, '2015-11-21', 'Mush better than my previous one Mush better than my previous one.  I only wish the bell that \"rings\" when the item is done was a bit louder.  You ne4ed to be fairly close to hear it go off  .I certainly hope it last a very long time.'),
(5838, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-07', 'So far, so good! So far I have made 2 bloody mary\'s and 4 smoothies and it is still running like a charm! Nice cheap little blender and does all I need. For those who experienced a bad smell of the motor ran out, perhaps ask for a replacement instead of refund? It\'s possible you got a bad one out of the bunch, but when you get one that works...well it works!!'),
(5839, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-20', '... maker about 2 years ago and it\'s been the best home brewer I\'ve ever had I\'ve bought this coffee maker about 2 years ago and it\'s been the best home brewer I\'ve ever had. It\'s easy to fill, easy to clean and makes a great tasting pot of everyday coffee. From the first cup to the last cup, the coffee never tastes burnt. If the day comes where it no longer works, I\'ll definitely buy another one of these.'),
(5840, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-14', 'Five Stars This Christmas present arrived on time and the loves it.'),
(5841, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-02', 'Five Stars Works well!'),
(5842, 3, 1, 4, '2016-07-07', 'Good but could be better Very roomy, controls are easy to understand, and looks good. In the older designs, the door is hinged to the rack.  as you open the oven door, the rack gets pulled out half way.  This way I don\'t have to reach into the hot oven to retrieve the hot item.  Miss that feature.'),
(5843, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-03', 'I hate cooking and this has really removed a lot of ... I\'ve been using this for a month and I have to say it\'s beaten every expectation. I hate cooking and this has really removed a lot of hassle for me. Pros: -Preheats fast. -Capable of anything a conventional oven can do, and in some cases more (as long as what you\'re cooking fits). -Timer auto starts after preheat, so I can throw my food in during preheat and walk away. -Provided tray is great, easy to clean. -Great build quality (minus buttons, see below). -Bigger on the inside (than it looks). Can cook a decent sized pizza (11\"). Cons: -Quality of the buttons leaves a bit to be desired, they are cheap plastic looking. Haven\'t had any issues with them, they just take away from the otherwise stellar looking machine. -Top of the oven gets warm. Hasn\'t been an issue for me but it\'s worth noting for people with limited space above.'),
(5844, 6, 1, 1, '2016-01-03', 'Burns Everything Even on lowest setting, burns EVERYTHING!'),
(5845, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-31', 'Cute little mini-maker. Perfect for two. Love this little coffee pot. Its so minature and simple, nothing has ever gone wrong. Fits perfect in our mini-house.'),
(5846, 3, 1, 4, '2016-05-28', 'Overall very pleased. Instructions initially were very confusing but I\'m slowly ... Overall very pleased.  Instructions initially were very confusing but I\'m slowly learning.  Very pleased with it\'s toasting quality.'),
(5847, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'Love the color Love the color. It gets compliments. It toasts and bakes quickly. Not the biggest, but it does the job. Nice to have a separate toaster function; my old toaster oven really toasted only one side of a piece of bread because it was an oven. The toaster slot easily accommodates bagel slices.'),
(5848, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-08', 'Hamilton Beach FlexBrew single-serve Coffee maker, Black. It is a wonderful new addition to my kitchen counter \"which is really a bit too crowded anyway\". The coffee maker looks nice and the black color blends well with most anything or any color you might have in your kitchen or dining area. Now, for the important stuff! This coffee maker makes a great cup of coffee, and in just a really short time. It takes about two to two and a half minutes to brew a cup of brew that will compete with any overpriced cup of coffee you might get at a commercial establishment. I like the convenience as well as the wonderful flavor you get from this so, so, simple to operate machine. It is easy to set up, easy to brew, and easy clean up. You could not ask for much more than that. There is a very large variety of blends of coffee single serve pods available at most all grocery stores. You can also get teas, cappuccino type beverages, hot chocolate, hot cider, and who knows what other items are available. You can also use the, re-usable, non- disposable filter to brew from your favorite brand or blend of ground coffee. The pods are quite a bit more costly than a regular type of coffee your 10 or 12 cup maker produces, but, unless you just have to have a pot ready at all times, these single serve pods are well worth the price when you consider the outstanding difference in the flavor, plus your cup of coffee is \"always\" freshly brewed.'),
(5849, 11, 1, 2, '2014-06-25', 'Toast level too high I have yet to toast a piece of bread successfully without burning it unless I stand there and watch it toast.  No matter what setting in the middle range I try, it always burns.  My last toaster oven did not do so, the dial was more accurate.'),
(5850, 5, 1, 4, '2016-07-25', 'Extra features like temperature choice of coffee Extra features like temperature choice of coffee.  Particularily like the rollers on the unit that make adding water easy.'),
(5851, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-31', '2nd one i\'ve bought. 1st one lasted me a ... 2nd one i\'ve bought.  1st one lasted me a year but then again it\'s not very expensive. But chops ice in smoothies surprising well for it\'s size.  Very handy to have on the counter'),
(5852, 2, 1, 2, '2016-03-11', 'Burns itself, not your toast It had the simple design I was looking for to replace a 13-year old unit that finally broke.  First oven showed up damaged from shipping but I still tested it.  The plastic & paint burn smell from this toaster oven was so strong that it choked me out of the room. The other thing I noticed right away is that the metal housing (unlike my old oven) is paper thin. This means the burn-through factor from the heating elements is extreme making this oven a hazard to have near anything or even touch by accident. The replacement unit showed up and I tested it as well. Again, the burning plastic & paint smell.  Ok, so maybe it has a break-in period? I don\'t care.  No appliance should have this kind of burn-off and it\'s a matter of time before some of the plastic components (like the knob on the back housing) melt off.  There is no way I\'m putting food in this thing with this kind of burn smell so I returned it and will look for something with a similar design but better construction.'),
(5853, 8, 1, 1, '2014-12-11', 'perfect for the pale brown, lukewarm water lover I sit here writing this review after not being able to make a decent cup of morning coffee, so I am probably being harsher than usual.  This is the worst coffemaker-ever. I got it on black friday for very cheap, I wouldn\'t like or keep it if it was free. It takes almost ten minutes to make a pot of pale brown lukewarm water. If you can\'t wait for it to finish, and try to steal a cup while its brewing, it runs all over the cabinet.  It doesn\'t get hot enough, it takes forever to brew, and the outcome is so disappointing.  I used to have a four cup Mr Coffee maker for years, and when it finally gave out I purchased this one.  I am returning this one asap, or possibly smashing it on my porch in an early morning coffee starved rage, and going back with Mr Coffee.'),
(5854, 3, 1, 2, '2016-08-19', 'Two Stars Hard to read not backlit.'),
(5855, 9, 1, 5, '2015-07-06', 'Great as usual Love this coffee pot no regrets lil bit of the big side but it works well looks nice Coffee is hot everytime very easy to program'),
(5856, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-26', 'Works and looks great! I\'ve had this coffee maker for about 2 months now and have no complaints. Brews quickly, no burnt taste even after sitting for an hour or two, easy to use, coffee is HOT. The wheels on the bottom of the unit are very convenient when filling up the water reservoir. I will note that it does not come with a water filter or the permanent filter basket that some other models come with. In other reviews I read before buying, I noticed some complaints of water leaking all over the appliance. If you do not make sure the water reservoir is pushed all the way in before brewing, water will leak and hardly any coffee will come out. Maybe that is the problem some experienced. Definitely recommend this coffee maker for those who want an aesthetically pleasing appliance!.'),
(5857, 9, 1, 4, '2016-06-20', 'This coffeemaker has exceeded our expectations! After years of ... This coffeemaker has exceeded our expectations! After years of making do with a Hamilton Beach,  we have finally found a carafe-less coffeemaker that does what it says it will do, with no drips and a light to show us the way!'),
(5858, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-22', 'Love love love Love this toaster! Sometimes it gets a little steamy, but that only happend the first few times and if it\'s something with a lot of water in it. It toasts really evenly and I love that it\'s not digital.'),
(5859, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'Great brewer I love my new brewer. The water resevoir is easier to refill and replace. I love that I have new color options. I have purple. There are many size choices from small cups to full carafes. The only thing I do not like is that my Van Houtte butterscotch kcups that I got from the Keurig site won\'t work in it. I get an error every time I try to brew one. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5860, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'love my new keurig I am a first time keurig owner and so far we really like it . it works great for everyone in the house that has different taste so we can have a good varity of drinks . thanks keurig for the free pods for this review!_'),
(5861, 5, 1, 4, '2015-10-02', 'Top Product The Good: -Removable  water reservoir is awesome, saves time and hassle. -No drip carafe is an actual no drip carafe -Also, doesn\'t drip from the filter to the hot plate while the carafe is out.  First coffee maker I\'ve ever had to accomplish this. -easy to read clock -easy to use buttons The Bad: -a little hard to clean carafe due to design i.e. nooks and crannies, and the lip where the spout guard is -wheels on bottom are for spinning the unit NOT pulling the unit forward as the ad suggests The Ugly: nothing horrible about this coffee maker, though we\'ve only had it about a week Overview: Future quality not withstanding, this is the best coffee maker I\'ve ever had'),
(5862, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-27', '... about a week ago and so far it\'s been great! It\'s cute I got this coffee pot about a week ago and so far it\'s been great! It\'s cute, simple, and works perfectly for such a great price.'),
(5863, 10, 1, 5, '2015-08-06', 'Good Product. Item just as described. Can\'t beat it for the money.'),
(5864, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'Five Stars She loved it !'),
(5865, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-07', 'This is the one. Feels like research and development did their job! Having owned several coffee makers through the years, I actually feel like an engineer designed this one. I seriously have no complaints. The price is fantastic too. My last big name Queezynart lasted 2 years and cost 2x as much. Coffee tastes just as good, no mess and is so easy...even when half asleep.'),
(5866, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'Great machine Nice looking machine, brews a great cup of coffee. I love that the water reservoir is removable to do a deep clean when necessary.'),
(5867, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-12', 'Love it! It\'s the perfect size for storage and for carrying! It blends smoothly even frozen fruit and it\'s way less noisy than my last blender which was also more expensive. This is a great product and you can\'t beat the price! Highly recommend!'),
(5868, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-11', 'Five Stars Excellent product and service.'),
(5869, 6, 1, 4, '2015-05-10', 'Great toaster. Has enough settings that are easy to ... Great toaster.  Has enough settings that are easy to read and adjust so everyone can have their toast as they prefer.  Only downside is that it toasts better on one side and less on the other.  Otherwise, very happy with the purchase.'),
(5870, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-15', 'Good deal Exactly the size I wanted and works really well. I get a little nervous about how hot the top, sides, and bottom of the oven get. The features are easy to use.'),
(5871, 7, 3, 1, '2015-08-02', 'When my last machine died after 3 years I thought I\'d try another manufacturer. This machine worked well for 21 cups or so, then it just quit. Something plugged in the pump system, no way to repair. In the garbage it goes and back for another Kuerig.'),
(5872, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-29', 'WOW... A product that works like it should ! Ordered this coffee maker to replace our old one(a Cuisine Art  Premier Coffee Series) which was still working (using the word working loosely) . Let\'s see ,I will make a comparison, old one vs. this one & you can come to your own conclusions: 1. old one,had to pull out from under cabinet to fill the reservoir--this one the reservoir is removable ,so you just pivot it 90 degrees,remove it, fill it & re-install it. 2.old one water reservoir was in the same housing as the filter basket & it frequently ran the basket over, filling the reservoir with coffee grounds--this one water reservoir is separate from the housing. 3.old one ,the pause & serve dripped on the hot plate every time you pulled the carafe out--this one never drips on the hot plate when you remove the carafe 4.old one,did not keep coffee hot in the carafe,heat plate not warm enough--this one has adjustable temp. on heat plate,when using the high setting ,coffee is good & hot til the end of the pot. 5. old one took more coffee to make a pot of coffee--this one has adjustable brew strength setting,allowing you to use less coffee. 6. old one, carafe dribbled on cabinet each and every pour--this one never dribbles on the cabinet. 7. old one, had to also pull entire coffee maker out to install or remove coffee filters--this one has swing out easy access basket. 8. old one,you could not read the tiny  black l.e.d display --this one has a lighted & easy to read l.e.d. display 9. old one cost $89 bucks--this one cost $44.99 on sale .  :) FOLLOW UP...After 60 days the entire electronics,LED panel went out and my new coffee maker is dead.Hamilton Beach says I can return it for repair or replacement but I will have to pay to and from S&H,which will be over $30 , :( .Can just buy another coffee maker for about $40 from store.'),
(5873, 3, 1, 5, '2015-11-19', 'Five Stars You made Gramma very happy'),
(5874, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-14', 'My Toaster Oven!! I love my toaster oven. Waay better than a microwave!.'),
(5875, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-20', 'Five Stars very nice coffee pot for my counter top.  Pleased'),
(5876, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-15', 'love this coffee pot love this coffee pot, easy to fill and clean, the light is great to see inside dark cups, a great improvement over my old cuisinart,'),
(5877, 9, 1, 3, '2016-01-31', 'Three Stars It works great but is less than what I hoped for.'),
(5878, 6, 1, 2, '2014-10-07', 'Two Stars THE TOASTER WAS GREAT BUT IT BROKE REALLY QUICK'),
(5879, 6, 1, 4, '2014-12-22', 'Four Stars Many nice features, but I am liking the cool to touch plastic body.'),
(5880, 2, 1, 3, '2015-04-17', 'I think its a great toaster oven I think its a great toaster oven, only reason why I\'m giving it a 3 star is that it is on the small side.  I didn\'t catch that when ordering from amazon.  the tray will barely hold 4 pieces of toast.  I would like this model in a larger size and then I would give it 5 stars.  I think it would be perfect for a kid in a college dorm, not for a family of four.'),
(5881, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-02', 'Very happy with this purchase We wanted a small toaster and are very happy with this.  It does bear watching as it heats up super fast!  It is great for toasting or heating rolls for sandwiches,  reheating pizza, etc.'),
(5882, 12, 1, 4, '2014-03-21', 'works better than I expected When I ordered this product , I hoped it would work better than the toaster oven that I had.  We tried to buy a toaster oven from a store, but they didn\'t  have one in our price range and tried to sell us one that costed more.  So we ordered one that Amazon had at a more reasonable price.  We found that the toaster oven that we got worked better than we thought at the price we paid.  Thank you'),
(5883, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'cheap brewer of however expensive coffee beans you buy it\'s a great buy! For a quick,cheap brewer of however expensive coffee beans you buy it\'s a great buy!.'),
(5884, 3, 1, 3, '2016-10-17', 'Very Bulky A bit complicated but it serves its purpose ... Very Bulky  A bit complicated but it serves its purpose. Wouldn\'t order it again.'),
(5885, 5, 1, 1, '2016-12-31', 'display cover has major defect! this item lasted about 1 week. when whiping one day the display cover fell off and one of the clip on tabs broke off and literally shattered. without the cover the display gets covered in steam (water) thankfully i got the replacement in 1 day, yey! but to my surprise the display cover already had the same exact defect when i took the item out of the box! returning asap!.'),
(5886, 4, 1, 4, '2015-06-11', 'Nice oven Agree the dials are difficult to read but the oven performs as expected .'),
(5887, 3, 1, 5, '2014-09-22', 'Five Stars Arrived as expected'),
(5888, 5, 1, 2, '2015-04-04', 'I really want to like this machine but bottom line TI really want to like this machine but bottom line--it doesn\'t make coffee hot enough.  And the highest setting of the \"keep warm\" option still has me zapping every cup in the microwave.  The other features are nice but I like my coffee hot.'),
(5889, 8, 1, 1, '2016-02-02', 'One Star doesn\'t get coffee hot ,,have to use microwave'),
(5890, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-09', 'Four Stars Would have given it 5 stars if the timer dial had a more accurate way to read the settings.'),
(5891, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-02', 'Great buy! Our oven in our home broke but this toaster oven is working like a charm!'),
(5892, 5, 1, 3, '2016-03-09', 'Cosmetically defective, functionally perfect It\'s a simple coffee pot. That\'s what I wanted. Easily cleaned, brewed and programmable without bells and whistles. 30 days after purchased, the faceplate snapped off. There are two screws at either side of the bezel that surrounds the buttons which were overtightened. Now, every time I open the grounds holder, it pops out. I\'ll put in some glue and see how it holds up.'),
(5893, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-28', 'Just what I needed! This was exactly what I was looking for now that all the kids have left the house.  It\'s perfect for the 2 of us.  I have been very happy with the quality of the product and the food it cooks.  At first I had to set the timer for less than the recipe recommended to figure out how it cooks, just like you would with a new microwave. This was especially helpful when I threw my back out and could not bend over!'),
(5894, 4, 1, 5, '2016-12-17', 'Five Stars excellent.'),
(5895, 10, 1, 4, '2015-02-13', 'It works great - 20-30 clicks and I have a delicious smoothie It works great - 20-30 clicks and I have a delicious smoothie. However... Personal blender - Yes, it is. With travel lid? Certainly not, because the lid is tragic. Not suitable for transporting - content is leaking through the mouthpiece during blending. I prefer not to think about what will happen during the movement. But hey, $15 for a personal blender? It\'s great!'),
(5896, 8, 1, 4, '2015-08-09', 'Four Stars Simple and will serve good for two.'),
(5897, 2, 1, 3, '2015-12-17', 'Works well; just too many buttons/knobs. Eh... works well, haven\'t had any issues so far. But too many buttons and knobs to have to twist and turn to toast bread... just want to put it in turn it to medium and hit start :) but like I said - haven\'t had any functionality issues.'),
(5898, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Coffee maker We use a Kuerig for day-to-day individual coffee servings.  We use this one for group gatherings where it\'s more convenient to prepare up to 12 cups at a time.'),
(5899, 8, 1, 3, '2016-10-26', 'Spout is too narrow to pour fast It\'s convenient to have this size in the office to share with my husband.  The only complaint is the design of the spout is such that pouring fast tend to spill.'),
(5900, 10, 1, 1, '2016-03-23', 'Not recommended for liquids... Don\'t get this if you want to make bulletproof coffee. With the cap firmly in place, and liquid no higher than the fill line, liquid spews out of the lid. Disappointing.'),
(5901, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Compares well with Cuisinart I\'ve got nothing bad to say about Cuisinart! Mine made good coffee for several years and presented few problems before finally misbehaving enough to make me replace it. I replaced it with this Hamilton Beach. The Cuisinart carafe even fits this unit, so now I have a spare carafe. Haven\'t had this long enough to know if it will last, but I will say it makes coffee that tastes as good or better than the Cuisinart. Started out with the \"bold\" setting, because I like strong coffee, but decided \"regular\" is just fine. I like the modular design of the Hamilton Beach. It\'s easy to operate and to clean. I like the swing-out filter basket. I like the removable water reservoir. I like the blue light! I like the simplicity of the controls. There\'s zero learning curve, just plug and play. It\'s ok that there is no beep to tell you when the brewing is done; the brewing is done when it stops gurgling, duh. It seems to require less coffee than the Cuisinart, but maybe the Cuisinart had just become tired. Best of all, it\'s a fraction of the cost of a new Cuisinart, even including the slight cost of the 3yr warranty which I bought. Happy with my purchase!.'),
(5902, 3, 1, 1, '2015-10-03', 'One Star works only part time at first now never what do I do to get it fixed??'),
(5903, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Works great. Love the water fill tank so you don\'t ... Works great. Love the water fill tank so you don\'t have to pour water into the machine. Definitely worth the money.'),
(5904, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Great product bought for my wife and she loves the ... Great product bought for my wife and she loves the color and how it brew what\'s she want thank you'),
(5905, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-18', 'Five Stars Excellent coffee maker this is my second one in 7 years ,There awesome'),
(5906, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-24', 'perfect for post workout shakes on the go Works very well, perfect for post workout shakes on the go.'),
(5907, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-15', 'Great! Bought it as a gift for my mom. She loves it!'),
(5908, 7, 3, 1, '2014-12-29', 'I received this as a gift for Christmas. This was the worst gift ever. First off, there is no size selection for the brew amount. Second, there was no steady stream of coffee ever during the brewing cycle. Only drips, spits and sputters. It made a terrible noise while brewing and shut off mid-cup. I had to press start again to make it finish brewing. Then, after my second try at it, thinking the first time was just a warm up for the machine, it started hissing and making a terrible choking noise again. I unplugged it after water started to drip from the top, where it wasnt suppose to be coming from. I let it cool for a moment and then after I pulled the tray out to clean it and put it back in the box to return, it started to POUR water out of the top which flooded the counter. Worthless.'),
(5909, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-22', 'Very good toaster oven. This toaster oven works great. It toasts very evenly (much better than my old one). The only negatives about it are: 1) the timer doesn\'t have individual minutes written in, just marks at 5, 10, 15, etc. so it\'s kind of guesswork as to how long you\'re setting it for 2) there\'s no way to \"save\" your toast setting (i.e. how dark/light you like your toast)--it\'s just part of the timer so it\'s hard to be consistent.'),
(5910, 5, 1, 2, '2016-04-02', 'Carafe Shatters Easily Looked forward to this premium-ish coffee maker.  Worked very well, coffee good.  Carafe shattered with a slight bump to the bottom of the coffee maker when replacing the carafe on 4th use.  Really a slight bump.  Checked Hamilton Beach website to buy a replacement. (BTW, currently none available, interpret that as you like) and with shipping replacement cost is around $20.  Hamilton Beach requires $75 purchase to get free shipping.  Went back to the Mr Cheapie coffee maker.'),
(5911, 4, 1, 5, '2015-05-12', 'Good size for our small kitchen and looks a lot ... Good size for our small kitchen and looks a lot more expensive than it was. The different settings are great as well. Very happy with this model.'),
(5912, 6, 1, 2, '2016-12-20', 'Two Stars Does not toast even on both sides.'),
(5913, 5, 1, 1, '2015-06-08', 'WARNING: DIED AT THE AGE OF NINE MONTHS We loved this product....until it inexplicably died after 9 months! Without any cause or indication that anything was amiss, the LED went out, and it was dead. Very sad. Of course, too long to return it Is nothing built to last anymore?  I guess we\'re talking about $5 a month of good coffee, but really???'),
(5914, 5, 1, 4, '2017-01-01', 'Decent coffee maker This is fast and makes a good cup of coffee. But sometimes during brewing it moves the filter around and the grounds get through and end up in my coffee. I\'ve had this a few months now and use it daily.'),
(5915, 7, 3, 5, '2014-03-09', 'I purchased this as a gift for my grandmother-in-law who received K-cups as a gift but no machine. I researched all products and for someone who doesn\'t need something complicated, this was it! you pop in, and push down. No other buttons! it was just what she needed.'),
(5916, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', 'Five Stars Not Bad.'),
(5917, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-01', 'Very Nice Toaster Oven, does a million things This is my first Toaster Oven.I should have started with an \"Easy Bake Oven\" Haha. This Product had taken an unfair beating & still works perfectly. For prior Toaster Oven users it\'s great. Just not for me.'),
(5918, 8, 1, 5, '2014-10-24', 'Five Stars Fast Response, product was exactly as described.'),
(5919, 5, 1, 2, '2015-06-22', 'This would have been better if it was a thermal carafe This would have been better if it was a thermal carafe. Works greats just make sure you use the 1-4 cup feature if you make that much coffee otherwise the coffee gets bitter. Update: 4 months after using it everyday, sometimes twice a day the coffee does not get hot. The burner is the only reason why the coffee gets warm. Really disappointed'),
(5920, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Five Stars Love this coffeemaker...great price when I got it.  Have never had a problem with it leaking!'),
(5921, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-02', 'I love this toaster oven So far, I love this toaster oven. Especially since I was considering a MUCH more expensive one. It heats up quickly, stays heated. I  baked brownies, using the convection setting and it cooked them perfectly and evenly. I don\'t think I have ever had my brownies turn out so evenly. It is easy to use. It does get a bit hot on the sides, but not insanely hot. Also, I like that it doesn\'t heat up my kitchen and house, as here in southern Florida, that can be a pain. I am using this quite a bit!! The oven itself, takes up a bit of counter space, but that is to be expected when you purchase a large capacity oven. I would say that it has the footprint of a small microwave oven. So far so good. I hope it lasts  me a few years or more!'),
(5922, 1, 1, 2, '2016-03-29', 'Immediate problems!! Spent 45 minutes on the phone with support when the second cup of coffee I brewed was full of grounds. The cup box is labeled with the Keurig logo and should have been compatible. I had run water through till it was cleared but the next cup also was full of grounds. It\'s working now.. Hopefully it was just a rough start! On a brighter note.. It\'s turquoise and really pretty!'),
(5923, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-17', 'Five Stars So far so good, easy filling of water and coffe.'),
(5924, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-11', 'Five Stars Perfect, just what my daughter needed in her little apartment.'),
(5925, 5, 1, 4, '2016-06-24', 'Makes great coffee, annoying condensation catch I love this coffee maker, but there\'s a weird little catch on the inside for the condensation, and you basically have to tilt the entire machine over a sink to dump it out.'),
(5926, 8, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'Five Stars ok'),
(5927, 10, 1, 1, '2016-03-07', 'Do not buy: Broke after 5-6 use Do not buy this product. The teeth of the blenders jar broke after 5-6 uses. When making tomato juice today, I heard a wired noise and when i check the bottom of the jar, i found that the teeth was loose and it almost came out of the jar. Buy a different product but not this one.'),
(5928, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-07', 'I definitely love this So convenient and does not take up alot of space, I definitely love this'),
(5929, 10, 1, 1, '2015-06-08', 'Dont get Doesnt work....doesnt blend'),
(5930, 1, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'Can\'t live without my Keurig! I love my new Keurig and use it everday! It\'s so simple, fast and easy and no more wasted coffee. I have also tried lemonade and cappuccino and they are good! Next on to teas! I always used a Keurig at work and knew I had to have one at home also. I love it!! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5931, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Five Stars worth the extra money!  High quality throughout. Door closing mechanism could\'ve been done a bit better'),
(5932, 7, 3, 5, '2016-06-06', 'Reliable....brews just what I want in under 4 minutes.'),
(5933, 10, 1, 2, '2016-04-17', 'Two Stars Not a great smoothie maker. the smoothie was coarse and not smooth.'),
(5934, 9, 1, 5, '2016-06-03', 'I would buy it again. Does an excellent job.  Fast.  Wish it were 14 cup.  Only drawback of not having a carafe, you can\'t fill a thermos or anything taller than a cup.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(5935, 5, 1, 4, '2015-09-02', 'I recommend this one If you are looking for a low cost coffee maker, I recommend this one.  I appreciate the choice of settings allowing you to make light or dark coffee.'),
(5936, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-03', 'Five Stars Thanks'),
(5937, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-10', 'I Love It _ I had the older version of this model and decided to upgrade. I am VERY happy. There are slight improvements which make it even better machine! I love it!.'),
(5938, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-06', 'Five Stars great coffee maker! reasonably priced and works great'),
(5939, 8, 1, 4, '2015-06-18', 'Four Stars Good .'),
(5940, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-08', 'Five Stars Best coffee machine ever! easy to use, makes great coffee, stays warm.'),
(5941, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-21', 'Wonderful! A simple, convenient coffee pot. I have a Keurig and I got sick of it. This little coffee pot does the job and does it well. It isn\'t fancy, but I love it.'),
(5942, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Works like a big oven, but smaller! I love this toaster oven. It works great when I want to make something quick and not heat up my over. It is quick and efficient and works exactly like my large over, just smaller! No complaints!'),
(5943, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-09', 'had the previous model of this and it worked great. This new one burns everything and the knobs ... NO THANKS. . . .had the previous model of this and it worked great.  This new one burns everything and the knobs are very difficult to operate and line up with the appropriate settings.  Also the clean out tray is in the actual unit which means you have to wait for it to cool down before emptying it.  All in all I\'d skip this model.'),
(5944, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-27', 'Five Stars Nothing'),
(5945, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-29', 'Toasty, not so much. Not toasting like expected, usable, but would consider not purchasing again.'),
(5946, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-30', 'Loving the bean from this machine We\'ve had this coffee maker for more than 7 months now and it\'s perfect in every way. Our small DC apartment has a tiny kitchen that affords minimal counter space for, well, pretty much anything. Coffee is a necessity in our home, so it had to fit. Its narrow design is perfect in our kitchen and will be, too, for others not wanting an appliance that is unnecessarily bulky. The water reservoir easily removes from the maker to refill and/or clean. The maker has tiny wheels on the rear, allowing for effortless mobility on the countertop. (I never even thought that (A.) I would ever type that sentence; (B.) That this would be a bonus feature that we needed.) The spout doesn\'t spill when pouring the carafe, the maker is easily programmable, it provides for a variety of coffee strength preferences (go bold or go home), and most importantly, it makes a really great cup of coffee.'),
(5947, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-23', 'best coffee maker ever Seriously, best coffee maker ever. User friendly and convenient and the coffee never tasted better.'),
(5948, 5, 1, 4, '2016-10-28', 'Four Stars This coffee maker works great, and is still working!.'),
(5949, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-21', 'Love! Works perfectly Love! Works perfectly, looks great in the office. Reservoir is a great capacity for us too, we don\'t have to refill too often.'),
(5950, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-15', 'This Cuisinart brews a great cup coffee and has a few features that I ... I have purchased 2 other brewstations from Hamilton Beach before this Cuisinart.  There is no comparison.  This Cuisinart brews a great cup coffee and has a few features that I really enjoy.  When I press the bar to pour my coffee there is a light that comes on so I don\'t overfill my cup.  The other model didn\'t have that feature.  It makes for a much cleaner delivery of a cup of coffee.  There is no leaking of water into places it shouldn\'t have water. The other brand leaked everywhere.  All in all I like its design very much and will not buy that other brand ever again.'),
(5951, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'I love my Keurig it\'s a simple and quick way to ... I love my Keurig it\'s a simple and quick way to make coffee and tea. I love the new bright colors that they come in. The touch display is a really nice feature as long as the new carafe. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(5952, 2, 1, 3, '2015-05-26', 'Bad timer control - just little nudge on the timer ... Bad timer control - just little nudge on the timer could be 5-10 minutes.  could burn your meal. otherwise its a good machine'),
(5953, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-25', 'Got With Nice packaging Very cool device works so super good deal take it fro amazon'),
(5954, 12, 1, 3, '2014-11-02', 'Three Stars insufficient instructions on operation of toaster psrt jack murphy'),
(5955, 4, 1, 2, '2015-12-26', 'stopped working after 16 months.  UPDATED review Like others, I liked this toaster oven until it just stopped working after 16 months.  It just won\'t turn on anymore. Since this was under warranty, Customer service very quickly responded with new toaster oven.  I had to pay $10 shipping and handling and they had me cut off and ship back only the old toaster\'s power cord-not the whole toaster oven, so that made it seem worth it since I generally really like this model-especially for the price point, and wasn\'t sure any brand lasts much longer than 3 years.  This is he 6th toaster oven I\'ve had in 20 years!  I used a silver sharpie to highlight raised black markings on dials, which ate really difficult to see.  The rack on the newer version was really tight.  it would have been ok if it was stationary, but since the door latches onto it so it pulls out slightly when door opens-it became very difficult to open and close door-especiallly as heat causes the metal to expand even more. Fortunately I was able to harvest the old rack from the old toaster before trash pickup.  The older toaster had a baking tray with a separate broiler rack accessory.  The newer one has a baking tray that you are supposed to slide under the regular toaster oven rack when you broil.  I don\'t often broil meat in the toaster oven, but I would find it very awkward not to be able to arrange and season meat on rack on the counter first and very annoying to have to wash the toaster rack immediately after broiling.  (eg I broiled a hamburger patty and then wanted to toast the bun)'),
(5956, 4, 1, 1, '2015-08-28', 'One Star Same cracked heating element issue. Low quality product in the end. Will not buy again.'),
(5957, 9, 1, 1, '2015-09-22', 'Coffee Relase Lever Already Worn Out! After 5 months of use the coffee pot drips all over the kitchen counter. Seems like the lever that releases the coffee has already worn out.'),
(5958, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-04', 'Made It Halfway Through Blending The First Smoothie and Broke I really should have trusted the other reviews - it broke during my first use of it (stopped working all together).  I had wanted a cheaper blender to trial and see if I would actually use it if I got something more expensive... but I guess this wasn\'t the right blender to go with.  I guess I\'ll just have to be satisfied with a partially blended smoothie for tonight...'),
(5959, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Great coffeemaker! No glass to break and the auto-clock ... Great coffeemaker ! No glass to break and the auto-clock works great .'),
(5960, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-20', 'Excellent Brew, Easy to Use! Have purchased Mr Coffee brand my whole life but decided to try something different and I\'m so glad I did!  The coffee produced my the Hamilton Beach is 100 times richer and much more flavorful.  Wish I would have gotten one sooner!'),
(5961, 3, 1, 3, '2016-07-15', 'I wish it was hotter Ours doesn\'t get very hot. Should go to 425 but ours only goes about 300. Good for smaller frozen and slow cooking items. We like the look but definitely rec\'d a defect'),
(5962, 10, 1, 1, '2015-09-20', 'Worst machine This worked only for 6-8 weeks and it suddenly stopped.'),
(5963, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-09', 'Great Product. Fantastic coffeemaker!  I bought this two months ago in an attempt to break my husband of his Dunkin Donuts habit - it\'s been a fantastic success and, even with the cost of coffee included, it will save us over a thousand dollars a year.  The programming feature is so easy and my husband loves waking up to hot coffee (and says this coffee is far superior to what he used to buy every day).  Very happy with this purchase.'),
(5964, 9, 1, 4, '2015-08-02', 'Four Stars The best coffee machine I ever had. Nice and fancy and I love it. Works well'),
(5965, 6, 1, 4, '2014-12-01', 'I have loved this toaster The toaster had a bit of a plasticy smell the first two times I used it, but it faded quickly.  Other than that, I have loved this toaster.  It\'s a great upgrade from my previous one that did not have a \"Cancel\" button or very good darkness adjustment.  I have not tried the bagel setting yet, but I anticipate good things.'),
(5966, 6, 1, 4, '2015-09-05', 'Four Stars I hear by give U a toast, Tiz the toaster that toast with the most.'),
(5967, 1, 1, 1, '2015-08-23', 'The box says 9 sizes but that\'s only if you ... The box says 9 sizes but that\'s only if you buy the K cup, the travel K cup, and the carafe K cup. I emailed Keurig to verify & it\'s true, you can\'t add the amount of your water to your cup that you want to, without 1) buying multiple size k cups or 2) using one of the 3 or 4 hacks that are out there. This is true of EVERY 2.0 system. Plus, Kuerig says they hope to have a refillable cup available by the holidays (2015). I didn\'t experiment with the ones that say they work with 2.0 - maybe other companies 2.0 refillables out there will work now.  I bought this for convenience, but it\'s not. I  returned the machine and bought a used, older model so I could choose my own cup size. When Kuerig created 2.0 it changed the software to give the company more control of your cup of coffee.'),
(5968, 2, 1, 1, '2015-09-27', 'I expected that at least it would toast bread. The least a toaster oven should do is toast bread - this one doesn\'t. It did for a few months, but then it began to turn off the element after a minute or two of toasting.'),
(5969, 5, 1, 4, '2014-09-28', 'Four Stars Great stuff!!!'),
(5970, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Best small travel bender! Best small travel bender! This is my second HB blender, the first one I took around the world several times until it finally gave out after eight years. I use my blender to blend my protein drink after the gym everyday while on travel. The machine blends constantly and powers thru even with crushed ice. Yes, the motor will smoke when working with non-standard current but you can remedy this by pulsing the machine. I suggest this little machine to anyone wanting a compact unit.'),
(5971, 5, 1, 1, '2014-12-31', 'One Star it stopped working after 2 months'),
(5972, 6, 1, 2, '2015-04-10', '... dial setting in order for it to even LOOK like toast - lesser settings do nothing Does NOT toast evenly  Dial needs to be to the maximum dial setting in order for it to even LOOK like toast - lesser settings do nothing.  Sounds and feels cheaply made.  So NOT worth the money!!!'),
(5973, 3, 1, 4, '2016-03-30', 'So far so good Has reheated our food (pizza), cooked frozen food (fish sticks) very well.  Kids still use microwave for fast results.  Need to use it more. But so far hasn\'t disappointed'),
(5974, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-25', 'I like it so much I\'ve been putting off buying a ... Mmmmm... I cant live without a toaster, I like it so much I\'ve been putting off buying a microwave for months now. Its a great little toaster. The warming option is a handy feature too. It looks sleek with the stainless steel and black and will go well with contemporary aesthetics.'),
(5975, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-12', 'Five Stars great for the  price.'),
(5976, 11, 1, 5, '2014-05-22', 'Great toaster oven and whatever else it does! Fab appliance, does it all and doent take up a ton of space!  Why I didnt have one of these before is beyond me!!'),
(5977, 7, 3, 4, '2014-12-30', 'I really like this because it uses k-cups and regular coffee and it shuts off after it brews I just don\'t understand why it was $35 online and $50 in the store'),
(5978, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-09', 'What a well designed machine! We are loving this machine.  It\'s so well designed that once you start using it you can\'t really forgive the fact that these simple features aren\'t implemented on every coffee maker out there.  We love the fact that it can operate under our cabinets without always having to slide it in and out.  Just spin it, grab the reservoir. fill, spin it, pop the door on the front, add coffee, go.  Other than that t\'s just a good solid machine that makes perfectly good coffee.  No hassles, no complications.'),
(5979, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-09', 'Gift Wedding gift They are very happy with it'),
(5980, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-19', 'definitely the best cheap coffee maker i\'ve owned definitely the best cheap coffee maker i\'ve owned! i may need to buy another one again in a year or two, but that\'s ok. i can\'t believe how well it does, compared to a drip over at least.'),
(5981, 3, 1, 3, '2016-01-14', 'Three Stars worked great for 8 months then just died'),
(5982, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-01', 'FINALLY A GOOD COFFEE MAKER Easy to read display, easy to set time and brew times after power outages, makes a great cup of coffee! (I should buy another and put away for the next one!)'),
(5983, 4, 1, 5, '2016-08-23', 'Excellent product Very good.'),
(5984, 4, 1, 5, '2017-01-27', 'Looks stylish and easy to use Looks stylish and easy to use. Makes great toast, steaks and even pies. I love not having to use my oven when I want to make something small.'),
(5985, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-27', 'Excellent so far! I\'ve been mostly pleased with this coffee maker since I purchased it several months ago.  I like the removable water tank which makes it so easy to fill.  I just pull it out, fill it with water directly from the sink faucet and then replace it in the back.  The controls are intuitive and easy to program and use.  I like my coffee kept hot and this unit has the ability to alter the temperature level that the coffee is maintained at and also has an auto shutoff timer.  The only slight improvement I\'d like to see is that this has a basket type of filter and I think coffee makers that I\'ve purchased before with cone shaped filters seem to produce slightly better tasting coffee.'),
(5986, 5, 1, 4, '2015-11-23', 'Performs as advertised. Performs as advertised.  Would give it 5 star but pot has to set on hot plate for a few minutes before it gets hot enough for me.'),
(5987, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-06', 'Five Stars excellent toaster'),
(5988, 10, 1, 3, '2016-04-03', 'not cool. The blades arent designed well I Very cute and portable. But for frozen fruit I now have to defrost the fruit on my counter for 30 minutes... not cool. The blades arent designed well I guess'),
(5989, 8, 1, 2, '2016-05-03', 'Until she told me it leaked I really liked it. Has been leaking for the past couple of weeks.  My wife has been wiping it up and just told me about it 6 days after Amazon 30 day return policy expired.  Until she told me it leaked I really liked it.'),
(5990, 12, 1, 4, '2015-10-27', 'Works for both Doors don\'t really close very tightly.  Toasts my bread fine as well as toaster oven works fast.  So with that one little flaw, I\'m still pretty pleased with the product.'),
(5991, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-09', 'This is great after having Keuregs and Kruups Paying a lot for coffee makers just never seems to be worth it.  This is great after having Keuregs and Kruups.'),
(5992, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-27', 'One Star wish i could send this back I thought I had cancelled all orders for this'),
(5993, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-06', 'Looks great and makes even better coffee. I have only had this coffee maker for a week but i already love it.  Makes great tasting coffee and the first cup tastes just as good as the last.  It has a really nice adjustable heat setting on the burner depending on how hot you like your coffee.  The no drip pot actually does what it states, does not drip when you pour.  Water canister and push button filter door are cool features.  Great all around coffee maker.'),
(5994, 2, 1, 1, '2016-07-09', 'Lasted 7 months Was awesome until it broke, started sparking and smoking after 7 months of light usage.'),
(5995, 6, 1, 2, '2015-11-01', 'It must have been made in a different factory than the ones everyone else is happy with. Uneven toasting and a bagel toaster tha this toaster based on a review in  C.R was just what I wanted. It must have been made in a different factory than the ones everyone else is happy with. Uneven toasting  and  a bagel toaster that  toast both sides or top and bottom if you prefer  is what I have to contend with. In my eighties and  burdened with  other problems  I didn\'t  notice within 30 days and the booklet said  a 3 year warranty so now maybe I will finally call and see what hoops I have to jump thru  because  I\'m  disabled  and shop on-line.  Or I could just throw this piece of  made-in China  s*** in the trash, go to a junk store and find one that works because it was made  to work by people who had one just like it  in their kitchens. And they  knew the factory owners name  and where his family lived because they all got together at the annual company picnic. They had cold fried chicken and potato salad and  fireworks because it was AMERICA!'),
(5996, 4, 1, 5, '2016-11-01', 'Five Stars Has met all of my expectations satisfactorily.'),
(5997, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-28', 'but so far great. I like the detachable tank where you fill ... Have use this only 2 days, but so far great. I like the detachable tank  where  you fill the water up- no leakage!!!'),
(5998, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-08', 'good little coffee maker does the job.'),
(5999, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'It\'s the best! By this price, It\'s the best!'),
(6000, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-29', 'great My son is enjoying this birthday gift.'),
(6001, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-05', 'Great product Works way better than a toaster costing three times more...'),
(6002, 3, 1, 4, '2015-01-20', 'Four Stars So far I love it. Cord could use to be a little longer.'),
(6003, 12, 1, 5, '2014-11-08', 'Use it almost every day - value for money ... Use it almost every day - value for money. Toasts bread, and can be used to heat up a slice of pizza, bake fish or chicken.'),
(6004, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-20', 'All I need is a small coffee maker and the ... All I need is a small coffee maker and the B&D suits my needs perfectly. You do need filters with this coffee maker.'),
(6005, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Great Toaster This might be the best toaster I have ever owned. It has many levels and it does a great job on toasting bagels. Like anything else, it takes a little experimenting to arrive at the settings you desire for toast and other products but after 2 bagels, I was right where I wanted to be in toastyness.'),
(6006, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-26', 'Five Stars Works great.  Fast shipping.'),
(6007, 9, 1, 1, '2015-01-24', 'Leaking $!#/ I\'ve always purchased Cuisinart but now hesitant. Loved the idea of single serve and loved the coffee  maker. It is larger  than normal. Anyway, I probably used it less than 20 times and it started to leak. Poured a cup and went back for seconds and the whole pot had leaked all over the  floor..what a mess. The lever wouldn\'t totally disengage . After much research on the Internet and Cuisinart was no help..I trashed it.'),
(6008, 6, 1, 5, '2014-04-02', 'Needed simple, got simple! I wanted to get a simple toaster after I deciding that I was wasting too much energy to heat my oven up for a bagel. I saw this Cuisinart and liked that it was compact, white (finding a white toaster in a store is evidently really difficult!) had settings for bagels and frozen items, and a darkness dial. I have used this toaster with frozen and room temperature bagels and bread, and I love it! I generally only keep it set to about 2.5 on the darkness scale because I only like my breads slightly toasted. But it gets the job done quickly and easily. I imagine if you put it on the darkest setting you would probably be eating dust. I originally used the cord storage underneath the toaster every time I used it to put it away in a pantry, but then I started using it so much more often and just decided to leave it on the counter since it doesn\'t take up too much space. The other thing I will note is that it does make a burning plastic type of smell for the first few uses. Just turn on a fan or crack a window if it bothers you, but it does go away and there is nothing wrong with the toaster. Love this little guy!'),
(6009, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-19', 'awesome works as expected, toasts evenly, excellent price, very pleased with this product'),
(6010, 12, 1, 5, '2014-02-18', 'Looks and works great! Very happy, looks good on my countertop. It has a nice feature, able to broil and toast, The low keep warm is a nice feature for a busy family.'),
(6011, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-13', 'Four Stars Best toaster oven I\'ve ever owned.'),
(6012, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-12', 'I love it , after 2 minutes you have a cup of coffee , very easy clean up .'),
(6013, 8, 1, 1, '2015-12-01', 'Save your money! Doesn\'t work! Bought this as part of a birthday gift for my mom and by the time she used it for the first time and realized it didn\'t work, it wasn\'t eligible to return.'),
(6014, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-20', 'Basic work house Small, standard toaster oven that does what it\'s  supposed to do well.'),
(6015, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-20', 'Five Stars It\'s great unit for what your paying.'),
(6016, 7, 3, 1, '2014-09-02', 'I wish I could review how it brewed a cup of coffee, but right now the coffeemaker is in its 30-40th minute sitting on my kitchen counter with its red \"ON\" light shining, with a mug full of water, some ground coffee, and a cup waiting to be filled. I tried all last night, tried again this morning, and tried again this afternoon. Unplugging, turning it off or on, and starting from the \"beginning\" all made no difference. The machine just sits there with its red illuminated switch glowing and doing nothing else. I\'m waiting for Hamilton Beach to reply to my email (they warn a 3-day wait), but I might just have to go back to Wal-Mart to exchange it. Yes, I\'ll exchange it. I\'m hoping this is just a dud because getting this will allow me to replace to machines taking up counter space to just one.'),
(6017, 7, 3, 2, '2016-01-26', 'I bought this 3 months ago and it seemed ideal. Much better designed and higher quality built than the other brands. Versatile as you can control amount of water per cup and use ground coffee as well as K-cups. However, in spite of light use, the internal pump has failed already. Know that Hamilton Beach will send you a replacement if you send them $10 and a photo of the defective unit with its power cord cut off. i went through a year of hassle with failed CuisineArt and Keurig units having to be returned again and again. If this one\'s replacement also fails, I will be done with K-cup brewers forever. They all break down too soon due to flawed internal design.'),
(6018, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-22', 'Best coffee make I\'ve ever owned. Still working great after 10 months. It is stylish with nice features such as removable water reservoir, flip out filter basket, and rollers on bottom. Update: Less than a week after I posted the above review, the coffee maker quit working. One morning it worked fine, the next morning it didn\'t. The display was lit and water was in the reservoir but it simply wouldn\'t start brewing no matter how many times I pressed the \'On\' button. I tried everything but no luck. I checked that it wasn\'t programmed to start later. I unplugged it and plugged it back in multiple times and I reseated the water reservoir. Still no luck. Since it was still under warranty, I contacted Hamilton Beach. Their customer service support was terrific. After describing the problem, I was asked to cut the cord and email them a photo of the unit showing the cut cord. I had to pay $12.99 by credit card for shipping of the replacement coffee maker but I thought that was reasonable. I received an email confirmation of my warranty claim and the new coffee maker was delivered in six days. I have no complaints with Hamilton Beach\'s warranty process or customer support.'),
(6019, 12, 1, 4, '2016-01-25', 'Not as good as the older version I bought the original version of this back a few years ago and loved it. I had to buy a new one, though, because the heating elements on the old one were not getting as hot anymore. This new version is nearly identical in function, if not in performance. I would have liked to have given it 3 1/2 stars. Four is a bit high. The one thing about the new one that I\'m not sure about is that it doesn\'t seem to get as hot as the old one. It seems that maybe the thermostat isn\'t as accurate. For example, with the old one I could bake a piece of salmon at 275 degrees for about 18 minutes and it was done to perfection. With the new one, it takes 20-25 minutes. So, I\'m having to re-learn all my cook times. Another problem with the new one is that it doesn\'t toast as evenly. It used to be that you\'d stick in a piece of bread and it toasted the same, top and bottom. With the new one, only the top half of the bread gets toasted. Another problem with the new one is that the door is crooked, so it doesn\'t close all the way unless I push down and then in at the upper left corner.'),
(6020, 5, 1, 1, '2015-09-01', 'WARNING!!!! DO NOT PURCHASE THIS COFFEE MAKER!!! WARNING!!!! DO NOT PURCHASE THIS COFFEE MAKER!!!! It will work for a couple of months and then it craps out. Just dead in the water with NO POWER getting to it what so ever. It happened to the first one I bought and I called hamilton beach to get a replacement which was like pulling teeth and then when they finally shipped it to me the second went out as well after a couple of months. I called them to get yet another replacement and they said I had to pay a $15 shipping fee. I was livid. I am still fuming about it and if this one they send me goes out I will NEVER EVER spend another dime on Hamilton Beach products!!!!'),
(6021, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-12', 'I honestly did not expect to be happy. After working in the coffee industry for 30 ... When I received the Keurig as a gift, I honestly did not expect to be happy. After working in the coffee industry for 30 years, I have become quite accustomed to drip brewing. The new keurig surprised me. With the ability to change strength and cup size, I have been able to brew a decent 16 oz. coffee. As with other reviewers, I do find that the carafe brew is a little to weak for my taste, but don\'t really need this mode often. Overall, I am very satisfied with the speed of brewing and quality of the coffee. Oh, and thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(6022, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-05', 'Excellent purchased Perfect size for countertop yet big enough to roast a whole chicken! Love that the rack slides out when you open the door.'),
(6023, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-01', '... fact that it was cute would mean it was poor quality, but it works even better than I ... I was afraid the fact that it was cute would mean it was poor quality, but it works even better than I expected! Love the option for toast or oven - both work great - I have used it every day since I received it - great combo appliance!'),
(6024, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Great coffeemaker Received this coffeemaker quickly and am extremely pleased with it!.'),
(6025, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-04', 'great little toaster Very good inexpensive toaster oven. Stylish look, easy controls, very happy with this product overall. It is strong. I was used to my old toaster oven which took three passes to toast a piece of bread. This toaster will burn a piece of toast if the dial is even set to halfway.'),
(6026, 6, 1, 4, '2015-07-25', 'The bagel booster is a good feature and I use that to get the crisp ... Doesn\'t toast evenly from top to bottom. The bagel booster is a good feature and I use that to get the crisp I like.'),
(6027, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-19', 'We love this! We had the last model of Cuisinart ... We love this!  We had the last model of Cuisinart coffee maker but decided to upgrade to this one.  We love that it has a light that shines inside the cup so you can see when it\'s almost full and can stop!  That alone is worth it!  We love that Cuisinart makes these coffee makers without a carafe to break!  This one has a \"clean\" button on it too!  We bought it for ourselves for Christmas 2015.  The Clean light just came on a couple days ago (8 months later) and we put the vinegar solution through and it all done!  There\'s no guessing when to clean it!  Love that!  Completely satisfied!.'),
(6028, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-22', 'Total waste of money We purchased this right before Christmas when out trusty one broke.  It hasn\'t been 6 months and it\'s about to go in the trash. Issues: The 1-4 cup function has never worked; it just keeps brewing and brewing. The small silver panel where the buttons are snapped off when we opened up the basket to put Ina filter.  The pieces broke and the panel will pop off if we don\'t hold it in place. The carafe has a weird lip on it that makes filling it up with water from a fridge very difficult. I wish I\'d gone with a more reliable Mr. Coffee instead.'),
(6029, 9, 1, 1, '2015-11-24', 'not happy!! Unless I figure out how to get the cord out of this machine I will be returning. It only will come out about 2 inches, then just stops, not happy !!'),
(6030, 6, 1, 3, '2014-06-12', 'Only average I can only give this an average rating because the knob that controls the darkness setting is poorly designed.  Even the slightest bump from anything will cause the setting to change. So you have to look at the knob every time you use the toaster to ensure it wasnt accidently changed.  A good design wouldnt allow this'),
(6031, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-30', 'Very happy Good quality and good appearance'),
(6032, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-30', '___ Addendum to previous review. Liked it at first but timer broke after a month...piece of junk! I\'d give it no stars if I could.'),
(6033, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-28', 'Five Stars Love this Coffeemaker.'),
(6034, 1, 1, 1, '2016-07-08', 'BOYCOTT 2.0 Keurings So VERY unhappy with the Keurig 2.0. They hold you hostage to using only THEIR brand of pod, thus increasing their profits while limiting YOUR choices. \"Customer Service\" HA! What a joke! Here\'s how to beat the 2.0 lock out!  [...]'),
(6035, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Five Stars Works really ell for the price !'),
(6036, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-26', 'Three Stars Much smaller than I expected - but will suffice'),
(6037, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-20', 'perfect for my small nonexistant counter space tiny little thing.  perfect for my small nonexistant counter space.  heats food much faster then my older larger black and decker that i\'ve had for ten years.  very happy with the quality.'),
(6038, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-18', 'Excellent Toaster from Cuisinart. Works perfectly every time, once you\'ve decided on the number you need to gauge your preferred shade of golden brown toast. Speedy and good results from frozen bread too. Lightweight design with simple lines makes it easy to stow under the counter and lift out for regular use. Very pleased with this toaster.'),
(6039, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-18', 'Five Stars great value'),
(6040, 3, 1, 3, '2016-04-18', 'Three Stars It gets WAY too hot on the outside. To the point that I\'ve moved everything away from it.'),
(6041, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-23', 'The best one yet Terrific coffee maker. Makes HOT coffee and FAST. Easy to clean, easy program to use, and the BEST part of all, the carafe is virtually dripless. First one in 45 years of coffee makers that doesn\'t drip! Yippee.'),
(6042, 6, 1, 3, '2017-01-21', 'Works just like the cheaper toasters! Well, it has lovely features that I\'ve never had, nice addition to the counter, BUT....like all the other thousands of various toasters it doesn\'t toast evenly at all!! Sometimes I turn it around if I remember, though in this day and age should we have to do this? I tried frozen waffles this morning. (Two slices, and parts of the waffles were toasty and one entire side was SOGGY, not toasted at all! What gives? I oven only have one slice of toast and can\'t figure out why this is a challenge as well? One side extra crispy, other side barely toasted. It doesn\'t make sense since ALL wires are hot! Can\'t they figure out how to make two slices of ANYTHING, given the extra gizmos?.'),
(6043, 5, 1, 1, '2016-03-10', 'One Star My item became brocken after 1 months of use'),
(6044, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-13', 'Five Stars It works amazing!'),
(6045, 1, 1, 1, '2015-09-09', 'Save your money and time. Had it for two weeks and just randomly stopped working. I loved the look but am so disappointed in the quality.'),
(6046, 6, 1, 2, '2015-05-15', 'DON\'T LIKE IT I had high expectations for this toaster. It let me down. I was hoping to get a major upgrade on the toaster I purchased for $12.95 in a discount store. The Cuisinart was being sold at more than 50% off retail. The two toasters looked almost  like twins. They were the same size. The tray from one fit the other. With the exception of the color, the two toasters were identical in appearance. There was not much difference on the inside. The heating element of the Cuisinart was 900 watts as compared to 800 for the off brand. This  allowed the Cuisinart to offer 7 heat settings as compared to  to 4 for the off brand and a slightly faster cooking time. However, this did not translate to a value that was double the cost of the off brand. The off brand was able to brown toast and frozen waffles and bagles in almost the same time. It seems that 4 heat setings is enough. The bottom line for me is that the cheaper dollar store toaster can offer the same level of service for much less.'),
(6047, 8, 1, 4, '2015-12-08', 'Small but mighty! It works good. It does not have an automatic 2 hour shut off.'),
(6048, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-22', 'Best coffee maker... ever. Best coffee maker.  Separate tank for water so ya don\'t have to open a lid, fill the pot and try to pour the water in without spilling it all over.  AND... it pours into your cup WITHOUT dripping all over - so ya don\'t have to hold over the sink every time you pour a cup.  This is the very first coffee pot I\'ve had that doesn\'t drip all over the place.  AND... you don\'t have to be a rocket scientist to program it.  All this and only 46 years after sending  man to the moon... what next?'),
(6049, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-25', 'Five Stars Very happy with my purchase!.'),
(6050, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-02', 'Best toaster/oven on the market I\'ve literally bought 3 of these myself over the years, leaving them with roommates when I moved on.  This is hands down my favorite toaster/oven on the market at a steal of a deal.  This thing cooks toast perfectly, and the oven heats up super fast and works like a champ.  I LOVE how easy it is to quickly (2-3 minutes even) reheats pizza and all sorts of other stuff evenly.  Just bought one of these for my brother this holiday season.'),
(6051, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-01', 'EXCELLENT coffee maker!! This is the second Cuisinart On Demand type coffee maker that I have owned. The first lasted over 6 years with serious heavy use. We are big coffee drinkers. We love this new model. It is very appealing to the eye and the coffee tastes great for a long time. I love the new feature of a light illuminating the inside of your cup, so you can see how full your cup is. The full/empty meter is dead on. I see that some people have rated this coffee maker poorly. I buy A LOT of Cuisinart products, and have found them to be superior without issue. As with any product, there is sure to be some lemons. I personally have never had any problems with any of my Cuisinart products which includes a blender, food processor, toaster, coffee maker, waffle maker, coffee grinder and a bunch of other appliances/bakeware. This is a 5 star coffee maker. LOVE it!! Also, READ THE OWNER\'S MANUAL AND FOLLOW IT!! I am willing to bet some of the people that are having issues have not read the manual at all. Follow Cuisinart\'s manual. They are dead on when used to the letter.'),
(6052, 8, 1, 3, '2015-10-23', 'Three Stars smaller than expected'),
(6053, 2, 1, 3, '2016-08-10', 'Love the size - not to large nor to Seems to be okay. Love the size - not to large nor to small.'),
(6054, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-26', 'Totally worth it Keurig 2.0 is totally worth the purchase. You\'ll save money in the end.  With each perfectly brewed cup- no coffee goes to waste and you get the right size serving every time.  I love my Keurig 2.0.  I wake up excited to get my cup of coffee brewing. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(6055, 5, 1, 2, '2016-10-18', 'Stupid design if one cannot find a replacement carafe. Nice coffee maker except don\'t ever break the carafe. I cannot find a replacement except if I pay $30 to Hamilton Beach. Annoying manufacturing that forces you to buy a completely new product if one item which is quite breakable breaks. Stupid design to make the interior smaller than any other makers so that only one small size carafe fits it.'),
(6056, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-08', 'Five Stars Love it...Good coffee at a great price.  hanks'),
(6057, 10, 1, 1, '2015-06-18', 'Junk Don\'t buy. Junk. The one we bought died just after the return period ended. No warranty after 4 weeks!'),
(6058, 12, 1, 4, '2015-08-21', 'Don\'t like that when you select baking mode instead of toasting ... Don\'t like that when you select baking mode instead of toasting mode the upper heating elements still come on when only the bottom heating elements should work for baking'),
(6059, 6, 1, 5, '2016-09-22', 'Five Stars works just perfect.'),
(6060, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-05', 'but once I got the hang of it is very nice. Also having a small oven for just me ... Took a while to get used to setting for lightly toasted bread,  but once I got the hang of it is very nice.  Also having a small oven for just me and not having to heat up the big oven comes in handy.'),
(6061, 4, 1, 3, '2015-05-17', 'just okay, not great The Cuisinart at $80 turned out better than the $20 Rival (which I hated!) that I bought to replace the broken toaster oven I had for about 15 years.  It was great.  I\'m still trying to figure out how to correctly set the timer dial for the toaster function on the Cuisinart.  I gave it three stars because  it\'s just okay, not great. Feel like this is another case of \"wish they still made them like they used to.\"'),
(6062, 7, 3, 1, '2016-11-29', 'have to pour water in as you use it ( 1 cup at a time) personally didn\'t care for the hassle. rather have reservoir and the perks. took back and replaced with a Cuisinart single brew'),
(6063, 12, 1, 5, '2015-12-24', 'Five Stars Compact, fits in small space, cooks fast'),
(6064, 8, 1, 4, '2015-08-19', 'Works Very Well For Me ... This is a great little coffee maker.  I had to learn to make sure that the top lid was snapped shut before brewing.  One minor problem I encountered is that this keeps coffee hot so hot that coffee has to be used right away or will burn easily.  Other than that it works really well for me and was at a great price.  4 1/2 stars.'),
(6065, 5, 1, 1, '2016-03-08', 'I was very disappointed in this coffee maker I was very disappointed in this coffee maker.  The coffee had a very distinct taste of plastic in it.  I ended up trying at least 3 other mid priced coffee makers with the same result and ultimately bought the Technivorm Moccamaster.  It was expensive but makes a great cup of coffee!'),
(6066, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-02', 'I like it If you are familiar with toaster ovens, you know how unevenly they can perform as toasters or they more dry the toast than toast it but, so far, this is the best toast result from a toaster oven I\'ve gotten and I\'ve had at least 10 of one brand or another over the years.  But it gets VERY hot so, you\'ll have to give a little space around the sides of the unit so things near it won\'t get hot. It\'s quite spacious for a low end toaster oven.  Nice width.  Wish it was a little deeper but, anyhow. There are 3 dials and, well, I guess that is a small complaint.  There was not a wide enough range on the bottom dial for you to see where you\'re going so, in order to get a decent setting for toasting, (which would be pretty low), you turn the knob just a tiny bit up but, because that setting is so low on the dial, you can\'t see it, you just kind of feel it.  There is a little bit of hesitation on the dial at that point so, maybe that\'s what that\'s about but, I wasn\'t crazy about that.'),
(6067, 11, 1, 5, '2014-05-19', 'Perfect toast every time I don\'t know why it took me so long to get a toaster oven. If are a toast dilettante like me, you\'ll be able to make perfect toast with this toaster oven.'),
(6068, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-25', 'Very Pleased I purchased this pot to replace a series of Cuisinart coffee pots which were having shorter and shorter life spans. The warming plate stop working 4 months after we bought the last one. We have been using this coffee maker for about 2 months and are very pleased with it. Makes a good pot of coffee in a reasonable amount of time. It is easy to program, fill the basket and fill the water reservoir. The wheels are small plastic balls that allow you to  glide the pot around in order to to make it easier to remove and replace the reservoir which is handy. There is 1 negative feature which is why I gave a 4 star review. There is a steam valve on the top of the unit which vents quite bit of steam during the brewing process which if you keep your coffee maker under a cabinet will condense on the bottom of the cabinet. After I set up the pot for the next morning I just pull it out from under the cabinet and the next morning glide it back under the cabinet. Wait until after you pour your first cup otherwise the coffee will splash out on to the hot plate. We bought 2 of this coffee maker. Since our pots have  history of working one day but not the next we like to have a back up. We intended to return the second pot if we weren\'t pleased with the first. We will be keeping the second. So now we have 2 pots that cost a little more than 1 Cuisinart.'),
(6069, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Five Stars Works great!'),
(6070, 7, 3, 1, '2015-06-20', 'Worked well for 5 cups, then started blinking with a reservoir of water. The instructions state \"reservoir needs more water\". The reservoir is still full. Can\'t understand why it thinks it needs more water. RETURN....'),
(6071, 7, 3, 5, '2016-07-26', 'great coffee maker'),
(6072, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-24', 'My mom said \"I\'m really glad you got this for me. It\'s the best coffee maker I\'ve ever had\". Bought this for my mom. She\'s retired and really loves her coffee, but also loves keeping things simple. So going away from the \"normal\" coffee maker was a challenge for her. To be honest, she didn\'t want this as soon as she saw it. But I asked her to give it a shot for a week and if she still didn\'t like it...i\'d ship it back to Amazon. 2 days later....she says \" I\'m really glad you got this for me. It\'s the best coffee maker I\'ve ever had\". I don\'t think I can add more to what she said. She really loves the taste of the coffee and it\'s a lot easier to use than she realized.'),
(6073, 8, 1, 3, '2016-03-03', 'Not Hot! Brews fine but the coffee doesn\'t stay hot.  Not thrilled.'),
(6074, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-15', 'Wonderful Toaster I finally have toast that\'s toasted right and delicious everytime.  Wonderful product.  I\'m sorry I didn\'t buy this toaster sooner.'),
(6075, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-16', 'Five Stars Very nice in our white kitchen and smaller than the older keurigs.'),
(6076, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Makes coffee and is easy to program Works well.  Makes coffee and is easy to program.  Pours without spilling.'),
(6077, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-11', 'Great Value, Excellent Coffee I\'ve spent the last two years brewing coffee in a percolator, a process I found to be imprecise and inconsistent.  Once it finally stopped brewing a strong cup of coffee, I decided to switch back to a drip brew.  This coffee maker was my choice, and the results were great.  The first pot was a strong, hot, and delicious cup of coffee.  Also, I forgot how nice it was to have an automatic brew feature, and the temp settings and brew strength programs were a nice touch.  I decided to buy the gold steel basket filter along with this machine, so I can\'t speak to its performance with paper filters, but already the machine has saved me a lot of hassle and brews a great product.  I don\'t normally give out five star ratings, but this machinenis excellent, and the price was nice, too.'),
(6078, 10, 1, 3, '2016-07-26', 'Bummer as I loved this unit Very dissapointed that one of the cups has come apart. The entire blade and bottom of the cup all of a sudden became \"unglued\" and made a mess. Bummer as I loved this unit.'),
(6079, 12, 1, 3, '2014-09-20', 'Three Stars Nice toaster and oven but has no crumb removing door on bottom.'),
(6080, 6, 1, 3, '2014-09-20', 'Meh Nice looking toaster by Cuisinart, but like many other reviewers have said, it does not toast evenly, especially with smaller or irregularly shaped bread.'),
(6081, 2, 1, 1, '2015-07-12', 'Cheap burns my toast I hate this toaster oven it burned my toast. Who cares about all the other stuff It can do if it burns toast! What is the point of a toaster oven that can\'t properly make toast!!! White or bakery bread even on the lowest setting for the least amount of time always burns!'),
(6082, 6, 1, 2, '2015-10-12', 'Okay toaster It is an okay toaster and to be honest it is not much different that a $12 one I got from the store while waiting for this one to arrive: They both toast my bread unevenly. Based on the reviews and the price I had higher expectations. But there are times that one side of my bread is burnt while the other side is barely toasted. I don\'t know why the new toasters in the market are so terrible. How hard is it to design a toaster with even heating. I never had a problem with my toaster of 10-15 yrs (which eventually stopped working). Also, the product arrived later than the estimated delivery date.'),
(6083, 3, 1, 5, '2015-11-18', 'Five Stars Fantastic Product!'),
(6084, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-30', 'Five Stars I am enjoying it at work. Plan to get a karate soon.'),
(6085, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-26', 'Great coffee maker to save space on counter As a design engineer I\'m pretty critical of electrical operation and design.  The fit of all the parts and ease of use of the controls are what I would expect for a product in this price range or higher.  I really didn\'t need the manual.  It is a very good choice when you are limited for vertical space and don\'t want to have to pull the coffee maker out to add coffee or water.  The only complaint is that the controls are right near the top where you hold on to the coffee maker to turn it around to add water...it is something I can live with.  And yes, it makes very good coffee for my taste.  Those who like a stronger cup, will use the option to do so.  Not sure what that does, but the stock settings work for me.'),
(6086, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', '0 and so far it\'s the best Keurig we\'ve owned Have been  Keurig fans for several years. My husband and I just purchased the Keurig 2.0 and so far it\'s the best Keurig we\'ve owned. It takes up little counter space, looks great and as expected the coffee is a treat to drink. We would highly recommend the Keurig 2.0 if you want a great coffee maker! Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(6087, 6, 1, 3, '2014-08-21', 'Three Stars This toaster does not brown evenly on both sides.'),
(6088, 10, 1, 4, '2016-04-09', 'Four Stars Good for traveling'),
(6089, 8, 1, 4, '2015-11-04', 'Perfect for me Perfect for me, the only coffee drinker in the house.  Feature I like, when you put the lid up, it looks like Darth Vader\'s helmet.  Disadvantage, you have to wait until all the coffee brews before pouring a cup - no auto stop.'),
(6090, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-13', 'It makes coffee. Great for a single person like myself. ha.'),
(6091, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-01', 'Four Stars Works'),
(6092, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-13', 'Five Stars love it.'),
(6093, 2, 1, 3, '2015-10-27', 'It works for my bagels and melted cheese I am afraid to leave this thing on for long, or to leave an open-faced anything in it. It\'s small and my insertable tray got weird after washing it in the dishwasher. The heating lamps are so close to the one rack, I (who admit to being a worrier) prefer the oven still for anything \"advanced.\" But this is a great little way to get your bagel fully toasted or melt a slice of cheese on bread quickly. And for the price, how could I honestly be unhappy? I can\'t speak to using it as an oven because that feels downright insane actually. (Especially given the reviews where handles came right off!.) '),
(6094, 8, 1, 4, '2016-02-29', 'Four Stars This item was a gift.'),
(6095, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-22', 'Five Stars good quality, fast shipping'),
(6096, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-10', 'Great value! Easy to use and easy to clean. Love the removable crumb tray.'),
(6097, 9, 1, 4, '2016-04-28', 'Four Stars Works just as it should.'),
(6098, 4, 1, 5, '2016-11-19', 'You need this oven! First toaster oven I ever bought. Over a year and it cooks grant and looks like new.'),
(6099, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'It\'s perfect! I love the fact that you can take ... It\'s perfect!  I love the fact that you can take the water container off to fill it so there is no more spills.  The feature of the wheels on the bottom is also an excellent idea.  I would recommend this to everyone.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(6100, 4, 1, 1, '2016-03-22', 'Poor quality and electrical issues abound We went through 2 of these ovens and both caught fire. We finally ended up getting a \"lesser grade\" toaster oven by a different company and it has worked far better than this. This one actually turned on by itself when we were not home, very scary!!'),
(6101, 2, 1, 1, '2016-01-01', 'Ours was a nightmare The timer stopped mid cycle resulting in a kitchen fire.  Good thing I had a fire extinguisher on hand.  If your timer stops, return it immediately.'),
(6102, 5, 1, 1, '2016-05-11', 'Face plate melted off Just after a few weeks, the front plate melted off.  Steam gets all over the clock and inside.  It is a cheap machine, I would not recommend to anyone!'),
(6103, 1, 1, 4, '2015-07-01', 'perfect for the coffee lover who wants it right away! This keurig is great! I love that they moved the water resoivor to the back of the machine. It\'s a slimmer model, so it fits better in the space that I had planned for it. I wish they would give more options for coffee sizes, or let you change water temps. Love that you can make a whole pot in this one. I received this model free for testing.'),
(6104, 5, 1, 1, '2015-12-08', 'Worked great for 2 months then the lid and its flimsy ... Worked great for 2 months then the lid and its flimsy plastic parts broke right at the hinge point.  To replace the lid it is 7.99 through the Hamilton Beach website but it is back ordered (probably because this is a common issue). This thing is garbage.'),
(6105, 12, 1, 2, '2016-11-22', 'I had spent years trying to get a nicely toasted slice of bread from a toaster oven Prior to buy this, I had spent years trying to get a nicely toasted slice of bread from a toaster oven, and I was never satisfied.  I thought this item would answer my need.  Perhaps there are better designed and built versions of this type of toaster oven that I should have bought.  All I know is that this one is poorly made.  The toaster works well, but there\'s no way to stop the toasting before the toasting cycle is up.  If you put it on too high a setting, or decide to toast your bread a little longer, there\'s no way to keep it from burning. The toaster oven door is poorly designed and constructed and doesn\'t close properly at least half the time.  The wire shelf in it is just a bit too small, so it doesn\'t slide in and out properly because it falls out of the \"tracks\" on the sides of the toaster oven. I\'m disappointed that this item is so poorly made.  I\'ve had it less than 6 months and I\'m already thinking about replacing it.'),
(6106, 5, 1, 4, '2014-07-11', 'It makes coffee and doesn\'t leak! When my about 8 year old Mr. Coffee bit the dust (or at least the carafe did and it was deemed toast), I decided to research quite a bit before replacing it. First thing I found was the coffee pot I had and was content with, didn\'t have great reviews! But it did have a leaky carafe and dripped on the hot plate..so maybe it did suck.. but back to Ham Beach, this was the model I kept coming back to. Liked the style, blue lights and stainless steel front. I really wanted the detachable container in the back for filling up with water, I felt like cleaning that holding tank out seemed cleaner than the normal unreachable depths on the back of your standard coffee maker. Not sure how helpful that is, but hey..it feels better. I also like the button popping the coffee ground door open. The carafe pours cleanly and I haven\'t had any drippy issues. This coffee pot delivers as promised, makes the coffee you\'d expect it to... and hot enough (though my girlfriend tends to still microwave hers to even hotter, so I suppose it may not be as hot as some would like!).  Haven\'t had trouble getting the timer to work accurately, though I feel like setting it up isn\'t as straight forward/simple as it could be. Dislikes: It came with a static cling sort of sticker on the aluminum like front piece, which left an oval ghost shape behind that drives me nuts! I\'ve cleaned it a bunch and you can still faintly see it. It\'s vocal... gurgles all ominously at you at random times, my old coffee maker didn\'t do that. And it doesn\'t beep at your to let you know when the coffee is finished brewing, I miss that feature. All in all I think I\'m satisfied and made a good choice for the price range and features offered.'),
(6107, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-06', 'Five Stars Works very well and fast!'),
(6108, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-05', 'Lots of controls on this toaster oven Really nice toaster oven with lots of controls.  Works relatively fast, (for a toaster oven).  Only issue, for toasting, it is very difficult to set the timer as you just barely set it and toast is slightly over done.  You have to keep your eye on the toast.'),
(6109, 10, 1, 3, '2015-03-24', 'Decent but not Recommended PROS: It works decently and chops up ice pretty well to make smooth and creamy smoothies. CONS: The bottom fills up with water in the dishwasher and there is only one cup. (I knew that when I ordered it but I still wish there were more) RECOMMENDATION: Buy a brand that comes with several cups (and one that has the blade attached to the lid instead of the cup itself)'),
(6110, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-26', 'Five Stars works great bought it last year still works great. we use it all the time'),
(6111, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-27', 'Five Stars Great product and came timely'),
(6112, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-25', 'Five Stars The best coffeemaker that we have owned, hands down!'),
(6113, 4, 1, 1, '2015-07-29', 'Now it sits in my garbage can. Lasted a year and a half. Heat sense failed. Indicator light flashed instead of staying on. No parts available to fix it. Now it sits in my garbage can.'),
(6114, 2, 1, 2, '2016-07-20', 'Two Stars Burns toast like crazy. Have to watch it.'),
(6115, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'It\'s the perfect smoothie blender It\'s the perfect smoothie blender. For real. I was skeptical at first. It\'s perfect! Was convinced by a friend to buy it, then I passed the good word on to my mom. To think I was going to spend big bucks on a bigger brand name. This works just fine. And since you drink from it, less to clean.'),
(6116, 12, 1, 1, '2016-11-07', 'I thought this was a great idea for a combo toaster and toaster oven I thought this was a great idea for a combo toaster and toaster oven.  However, the oven feature does not work well.  It doesn\'t seem to retain the heat temperature and food does not get cooked enough.  Also the oven space is very small.  You cannot cook much more than something for one person.  It works ok as a toaster, but I wouldn\'t recommend.'),
(6117, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-06', 'I couldn\'t be happier with my purchase I have always been a little leary of buying these kinds of brewing systems before but recently gave into and purchased one, I couldn\'t be happier with my purchase! This system is fantastic, I wish I had broken down and purchased one sooner. It\'s such an easy system to use, no more measuring the coffee when I\'m ready to brew, no more having to remember to turn my system off after brewing, you simply pop in the coffee you want brewed step away to do other tasks and come back shortly and there is your coffee waiting on you. It\'s a fantastic system and I have really enjoyed my Keurig, well worth the money spent! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review'),
(6118, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'It\'s great having the option to just brew a cup or ... We are loving this new Keurig. It\'s great having the option to just brew a cup or a whole pot when we have company over. I also like that it gives you the brew sizes in ounces where as the other one I have did not tell you the ounce size on the screen. Truly love how simple the keurig makes life and breakfast. Thank you Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
