(6140, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-02', 'It is great, the blue light is a little annoying It is great,the blue light is a little annoying.'),
(6141, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-27', 'Consistently even toasting I bought this for my daughter, who is furnishing her first apartment. She is a toast fanatic, so I was careful in my selection. She has been delighted with this toaster, in fact preferring it to mine, which cost at least twice as much. Unlike my toaster, this one toast evenly on both sides consistently. It\'s faster and easier to use the dial to adjust the toasting level than it is to press digital buttons, which so many models have these days. And the slots on this toaster are a great size, accommodating bagel halves and toasting most kinds of bread slices right up to the top, even if they are slightly oversized. Also important  it is compact and does not take up too much of the counterspace in an apartment sized kitchen.'),
(6142, 5, 1, 4, '2016-05-19', 'Four Stars this is the best one I have ever had. it does not over heat the coffee'),
(6143, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-23', 'Four Stars Great quality, works great'),
(6144, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-23', 'I have used for heavier things as well and works awesome! Only blender I have. Use it mainly for protein shakes. However, I have used for heavier things as well and works awesome!'),
(6145, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-06', 'Five Stars Needed a smaller toaster over for kitchen counter, this fits perfectly.....'),
(6146, 6, 1, 1, '2017-01-02', 'Doesn\'t get hot enough Even with the dial on the highest setting, the toast has to be put through 2 cycles to get toasted. Also, as others have said, it doesn\'t toast evenly. This wouldn\'t bother me as much if it would get hot enough to toast the bread sufficiently with 1 cycle. I can\'t imaging why one would need levels 1-6, unless there is quality control variance issues with these toasters.'),
(6147, 5, 1, 3, '2015-07-16', 'Died after 5 months Totally died after 5 months but liked it before it failed.'),
(6148, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'Good HOT Coffee - CAN USE NEW RE-USABLE PODS WITH OWN COFFEE!! I recently purchased the K250 and have been extremely satisfied with the product. -Smaller Brewer: I chose it because it was slimmer than the other options and was reasonably priced. -Water Capacity: Since it is a smaller option, the water capacity is significantly smaller compared to other models, but is is large enough for 1-2 consumers/day. -Lack of Auto features: It takes some time to preheat for the first brew and in between immediate consecutive brews but not any longer than previous models. -Touch Screen: The touch screen works well and is easy to use. -Re-Usable Pods: The big selling point for me is that you can use your own coffee with a re-usable pod. I purchased the Eco-Fill 2.0 Deluxe and it has been working perfectly with the new 2.0 Keurig. -Brewed Coffee: Brewed coffee and water is HOT which is very important for me as well. Overall I would recommend this product for individuals as long as they don\'t mind compromising on water capacity and the lack of auto on/off feature. Thanks, Keurig, the free pods for this review.'),
(6149, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-24', 'Five Stars Fair price !'),
(6150, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-31', 'Good product Does everything you want a toaster oven to do. Perfect size for 2 of us.'),
(6151, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-16', 'Bad Product Bought it a few months ago, drips very slowly ( Even after doing their cleaning instructions) and not having coffee hot anymore when dripping  Not a good product'),
(6152, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-05', 'Excellent. I got tired of the expensive k-cup machines ... Excellent. I got tired of the expensive k-cup machines and wanted something more simple. It has one button and it makes coffee. Period. Cheap, effective, convenient, and quick. The only thing I recommend is that you clean it out a few times and run the machine with just water prior to use. (When it is brand new some of the plastic smell sticks with the coffee) But I was anticipating that to happen and after cleaning it, it is perfect! Better coffee than k-cups, just as fast, and cleaner.'),
(6153, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'Hamilton Beach Coffee pot Very satisfied with my coffee potential'),
(6154, 10, 1, 5, '2015-08-06', 'Five Stars Good product.'),
(6155, 5, 1, 4, '2016-01-21', 'Great coffee maker! I bought this about a week ago and so far so good - I love this coffee maker. It\'s very quiet when it brews, the programming is easy and the best thing is when you pour the coffee it pours nice and fast and doesn\'t dribble. We had two Cuisinart coffee makers before this and both of them worked well except they both dribbled when you poured the coffee. The worst thing is they both broke after about a year of daily use. I will give this one a 5 star after a year. ;)'),
(6156, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-03', 'Great inexpensive toaster Lightweight, easy to handle and toasts evenly. It\'s not the fastest toaster but certainly as efficient as toasters I have paid 3 times as much for.'),
(6157, 5, 1, 4, '2016-03-06', 'Good and  loud The only reason this isn\'t getting 5 stars...Loudest coffee pot ever.  I mean, wake you out of a dead sleep loud.  Other than that, we\'ll thought out features and makes a decent pot of coffee.  Loudly.'),
(6158, 5, 1, 3, '2015-01-23', '... maker did not leak it would have been a great coffee maker If the coffee maker did not leak it would have been a great coffee maker. Hamilton Beach had great little ideas that they built into the maker. This is the seconds hamilton Beach coffee maker that I have bought. The first one lasted about a year. This one lasted 1 & a half weeks.'),
(6159, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-01', 'great oven Bakes, makes toast in short time. Convection feature works well in bake mode for even cooking.'),
(6160, 5, 1, 1, '2014-10-05', 'The coffee just does not taste good compared with other coffee pots - which is a ... After a month the lettering on the buttons has worn off. The coffee just does not taste good compared with other coffee pots - which is a shame as we like the removeable container to fill the water. It is a shame that this is past the return policy.'),
(6161, 2, 1, 4, '2015-11-10', 'Love this Got this for a great price. Nice addition to the kitchen. Small and portable and great for more than 4 slices.'),
(6162, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-30', 'Five Stars I like the ease of cleaning the water reservoir.'),
(6163, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-26', 'Was a good price, too Works well and is a 5-cup carafe instead of 4-cup. Was a good price, too. I recommend it.'),
(6164, 5, 1, 2, '2016-07-26', 'This coffee maker was fantastic.. This coffee maker was fantastic... for the 2 weeks it worked. Would never buy again. Several other reviews mentioned the problem of not working past a few weeks. Avoid the headache and pay up for a higher quality machine.'),
(6165, 3, 1, 2, '2015-07-08', 'Pass On This  Black & Decker CTO6335S Toaster Oven I appreciate Amazon.com but I do not think you should buy the Black & Decker CTO6335S Toaster Oven from this site. My unit is a factory return, not new. All of the packaging has damage and other signs of abuse. The oven is slightly dented on it\'s top right section. Some grubby fingerprints were noticed on the left side and on the glass door. My oven is crudely built, a bit like a tin wind-up toy. The unit is not double jacketed or heat-shielded well. You should not put anything on top of the unit or leave it under a cabinet when in use. Careful, the oven rack has no retainer, it slides right out. Next time, I hope I can afford another Cuisinart toaster oven.'),
(6166, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love it It makes coffee the fastest, the easiest. Looks nice and is easy to clean'),
(6167, 3, 1, 1, '2016-07-30', 'Caveat Emptor After about 6 months of light use, this Black & Decker convection oven simply quit working. It would heat up just fine, then immediately turn off, as in dead. Dead like a dead parrot. It ceased to register life, even the power light, the very signifier of life. Please don\'t suggest it  it had anything to do with the timer as this was my initial thought. \"Oh, the timer must have been set for two minutes and it simply turned off, as the timer would dictate.\" No, after unplugging it and plugging it back in a couple of times (because, hey, restarting always works when I have issues with my Mac), punching numerous buttons (some without anger), and cursing it out, I surmised I wasted $68 on a stainless steel hunk of junk. Maybe I should\'ve been tipped off by the suspect Black & Decker logo on the front. It doesn\'t look like the B & D logo so familiar to all of us. Perhaps the sweat shop it was made in didn\'t have legal rights to use the original logo as the company wished to distance itself from a factory turning out inferior products. Or perhaps I just bought a lemon in the guise of a convection oven. Other folks gave this convection oven good reviews. I wish I could count myself among these lucky buyers. Sadly I cannot, nor did I retain the receipt or have the patience to try to get a refund or, gasp, an exchange. The silver lining is I can use the small pan that came with it in my next convection oven, which will not be made by \"Black & Decker\". Small solace, but, unlike the oven, it works just fine.'),
(6168, 6, 1, 1, '2015-05-07', 'One side burns Well, maybe mine was defective but I don\'t think so. I tried all settings on two slices, and one on either side, and it still burned one side while barely browning the other. The temp setting on two out of nine even burned one side. Bagel setting didn\'t do jack. It was very fast and I\'m guessing it is just too hot - on one side that is.'),
(6169, 4, 1, 3, '2016-10-16', 'Three Stars Nice for price. Cord is undersized, gets hot near plug. Rack tends to stick.'),
(6170, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-14', 'works great. I would prefer a toaster oven that pulls the tray out as you open the door. Otherwise, works great.'),
(6171, 6, 1, 2, '2015-05-14', 'Read before you order So I searched for Best Toaster on Amazon and this model came up.  But after using it a few times, discovered that 1 side of the bread was toasted correctly but way light on the other.  Decided to take a look at the reviews in detail, focusing on the most recent first.  To my dismay, most of them focussed on this same issue.  Amazon graciously agreed to allow me to return it and I ordered a different model, also highly rated but without this persistent problem'),
(6172, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Five star This is the second one I have owned. The first one got taken out by a lightning strike. I did not hesitate to buy another one. I love this coffee maker. It is simple to operate, makes great coffee, and is stylish. What\'s not to love?'),
(6173, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'Best purchase we made. Love all the updates on the coffee maker. Light at dispenser area helps eliminate overflow. Water fill area made clear also make this so much better. Used by a 69 year old daily and much simpler to use than the model we purchased 5 years ago.'),
