(6188, 1, 1, 1, '2016-10-17', 'Wouldn\'t Purchase the 2.0 Again I was excited to purchase the new Keurig 2.0 brewer for my husband for Christmas after having the K55 for a couple years.  We were quite pleased with the K55, but wanted a smaller model for the kitchen counter.  Unfortunately, the 2.0 has really disappointed us, as we\'ve had trouble - many instances of differing fill levels despite what button has been selected, coffee with lots of grounds in it, and water pressure errors with grounds spewing out into the cup, despite using Keurig branded K-cups and cleaning as directed. I would not buy this one again, and I wish I would have returned it when we first had issues, because it has only gotten worse.  Additionally, the water reservoir seems smaller and is more of a pain to fill and replace due to its shaping.'),
(6189, 9, 1, 4, '2016-12-04', 'I like not having a glass carafe I like not having a glass carafe.  However, the water \"holder\" is heavy and awkward to fill up and replace.  The removeable piece (to fill taller mugs) still does not allow for tall mugs or travel mugs. Even though I\'m OK with this unit, next time, I will opt to spend more money and get a more user-friendly coffee maker.'),
