(6204, 5, 1, 1, '2014-10-24', 'This is the worst coffee maker I have owned in the past 30 ... This is the worst coffee maker I have owned in the past 30 years.  I have owned this for a year now and am looking to replace it.The coffee comes out warm, not hot, takes forever to brew.  Not to mention when it finishes, there are coffee grounds that end up in the cup.  The filter is still full of water/coffee/wet grounds, when I go to empty it. The water tank is in the back, which is good if you keep your pot on the counter alone, we keep it on the counter, but have cabinets above it, so we have to move the pot each day to fill it. I like nothing about this pot.'),
(6205, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-03', 'Five Stars Great coffee-maker and easy to program!'),
(6206, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Great product! I had an older model Keurig before this one. In comparison the 2.0 k200 is faster, more compact, and I love the touch screen! You can choose between, 4, 6, 8, or 10 oz cups. There is also an option to brew the coffee strong. Cons: No option to brew a 12 oz cup, you have to buy an upgraded model for that. It also doesn\'t hold a lot of water in the tank. Overall I definitely recommend this product, especially if you\'ve never had a Keurig before. I received this product free for testing purposes.'),
(6207, 10, 1, 2, '2015-04-23', 'Two Stars Not as powerful'),
(6208, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'GOOD COFFEE VERYTIME Very good coffee, easy and reliable. The pivot built in wheels are a really nice convenience for filling the water reservoir.'),
(6209, 11, 1, 4, '2014-07-22', 'Four Stars This toaster is a matte brushed nickel type finish and not chrome as I assumed incorrectly.'),
(6210, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-05', 'best investment ever Seriously, best investment ever. I bought this after having my first kid. My husband works a lot so I am home a lot with a screaming baby. I started having a hard time keeping my eyes open let alone take care of a newborn alone. I ordered this because it was cheaper than the one art Wal-Mart. It works wonderfully! Its almost identical to one we had at work but I love that you can see how much water is in it because for some reason I always over filled the one at work (coffee every where) not with this one. I did find the power button weird ( pushed down is on pushed up is off) but figured it out the second I plugged it in :) . I\'ve been using it for a couple months and no hard water issues yet. It also comes with cleaning instructions to do once a month to prevent hard water build up. Which is super nice. Sometimes after it brews once I dump it back in to brew again so that its more like espresso and I use it to make my own version of Starbucks drinks. Its delicious!'),
(6211, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-24', 'Mine works great.. Got two of them..one for mom and i know she likes it..Mine works great...I wish one thing they could of done is put a clock in the oven..'),
(6212, 5, 1, 1, '2016-07-23', 'Broke after the first day. Returned it. Front ... Broke after the first day.  Returned it.  Front panel popped of and a button came out that could not be fixed.'),
(6213, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'LOVE IT!!!! LOVE, LOVE, LOVE it!!!!!!!  I would definitely recommend this product.  Absolutely NO problem with leaking (like I read in some reviews).'),
(6214, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-27', 'As advertised As advertised'),
(6215, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-17', 'Short and Sweet This toaster does everything I ever needed it to do. Before I bought this I used to have to heat up my oven and then toast whatever. This basically flash-toasts whatever I put into it.'),
(6216, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Five Stars My third one in 9 years.'),
(6217, 9, 1, 1, '2016-09-23', 'DO NOT BUY, DEFECTIVE I got this in July of 2016, used it for a couple weeks then the seal that keeps the coffee from leaking out all over the place broke.  It was within the month warranty, so I sent it back for a replacement.  The replacement one worked for 5 weeks, then the same seal broke, rending this unusable, but sadly, it\'s past the warranty date so I must throw it away and purchase something else.  DO NOT BUY THIS, IT\'S DEFECTIVE (I TRIED IT TWICE).  YOU WILL BE WASTING YOUR MONEY.  :(.'),
(6218, 7, 3, 2, '2015-01-21', 'I do but don\'t recommend this. It says in the description \" The Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffeemaker allows the flexibility of brewing freshly ground coffee one minute\". That is not true! It took almost 5 minutes for an 8oz cup. If you are NOT looking for a 1 minute cup brew, then it may be for you. Also, my coffee mugs are 4 1/2 inches tall and will not fit on the Multilevel Cup Rest. Very disappointed overall. I was looking for a less expensive coffeemaker that the Keurig and guess I got what I paid for!!! I will probably return this and buy the Keurig.'),
(6219, 2, 1, 2, '2016-08-18', 'Skin Scorch Hot Two observations.  The unit top gets extremely hot when toasting bread.  I placed the tray on the top while toasting and it became skin scorch hot as did the metal top.  The oven sits on top of my microwave and is four inches beneath the cabinet which is worrisome and could be a fire hazard - I suspect I\'ll  have to trash it and take the loss.  My previous oven a Europro and years earlier two similar B&D ovens did not exhibit this problem  The toasting was the first thing I did after receiving it - doubt I\'ll try any baking or broiling.  Obliviously a manufacturing cost saving improvement. Second - the temp. setting knob is easy to turn clockwise and very tight turning back counterclockwise. It may loosen up after time if I were to keep the oven.'),
(6220, 2, 1, 3, '2015-03-25', 'on toast: bottom will be significantly more \"toasted\" than ... on toast: bottom will be significantly more \"toasted\" than top, and have grill marks of \"non-toasted\" lines if using the tray, the bottom will be significantly less \"toasted\" than the top otherwise, performs well, haven\'t had a problem with it yet'),
(6221, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-02', 'Wow! Perfect toast every time. This is my favorite kitchen appliance and lets me have healthy snacks on perfectly toasted bread 24/7.'),
(6222, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-25', 'There is always about a 1/8th of a cup of coffee wasted at the bottom Only comment I have (and note that it doesn\'t take away from it being 5 star) is that the mouth to the carfare is designed such that it won\'t allow for the complete emptying of its contents. There is always about a 1/8th of a cup of coffee wasted at the bottom. You have to rinse it out and shake it vigorously upside down to get it completely empty.  Not a huge deal, just an observation.'),
(6223, 2, 1, 2, '2016-06-03', 'Not good for much except making toast The inside dimensions of this are really small. Much smaller than older models with the same outside dimensions. Not good for much except making toast.'),
(6224, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-22', 'Five Stars Very easy to use.'),
(6225, 5, 1, 2, '2016-08-25', 'As another customer posted the front plate came off within ... As another customer posted the front plate came off within a week.  Called Hamilton Beach and they replaced with a different coffee maker.'),
(6226, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-27', 'Five Stars Makes great coffee'),
(6227, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-30', 'Great Toaster Oven My old one finally conked out and this is the replacement. I love it! Works great and has even more settings. Cooks and toasts evenly.'),
(6228, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-28', 'Strong coffee....not this one. Works well....no problems.  However, I don\'t like the fact that I can\'t make my carafe coffee strong.  The only thing you can brew strong is a single cup.'),
(6229, 5, 1, 5, '2016-12-02', 'Five Stars I love the water reservoir system, so nice! Very usable  machine, has everything I need.'),
(6230, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-30', 'The first time I used it, my toast burst ... The first time I used it,  my toast burst into flames. When I called Black and Decker the customer service rep blamed me fire not watch the toast taost.'),
(6231, 2, 1, 3, '2016-05-10', 'and the front door falling open) are annoying when you know there\'s a better toaster out there Does the job and is cheap to buy; however we were spoiled by our last toaster (Cuisinart) and looking back should have spent the extra $30 for it. Small things (like how to \"time\"\' your toast, and the front door falling open) are annoying when you know there\'s a better toaster out there.'),
(6232, 2, 1, 1, '2015-04-29', 'Handle melted within a month of use The handle of the toaster melted within one month during use. I would not recommend buying this product.'),
(6233, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-28', 'happy with purchase very nice product, works great, roomy, like that you can broil with it. removable tray and easy cleaning too.'),
(6234, 9, 1, 4, '2015-03-19', 'Love this coffee pot but hate the new shorter cord Love this coffee pot but hate the new shorter cord, it needs to be 5 inches longer. I understand the safety feature of a short cord, but not this short. The company needs to make a retractable cord if they want to make a safety feature. They tell you in the directions that you can use an extension cord if you have to, but that compromises the safety feature of a short cord in the first place. So in order to use my new coffee pot I will have to go looking for a short extension cord. Makes no since to me.'),
(6235, 8, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', 'Five Stars It makes coffee.'),
(6236, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-20', 'Five Stars love the fuel gauge.'),
(6237, 5, 1, 2, '2016-01-21', 'Fragile carafe, expensive replacement. This is a pretty good coffee maker, but the carafe is very fragile; a piece broke out of it during the second washing. I wanted to buy a replacement from Amazon but it\'s not clear that the ones sold here will fit this model. Also, it\'s not eligible for Prime free shipping. I checked out the Hamilton Beach website. From them, it\'s only $13.99 but the cheapest shipping option is more than the cost of the carafe!  I\'m very disappointed.'),
(6238, 5, 1, 1, '2015-05-03', 'Doesn\'t work for us. Unfortunately this coffee maker never worked right for us. I just checked and unfortunately the return window closed a week ago. The coffee doesn\'t brew properly. Water gets backed up and spills out over the top of the pot. When I pull the pot out to pour a cup before the brewing process is completed, coffee keeps pouring out. I thought we could manage the problem by making sure the pot is pushed firmly against the back of the coffee maker, but that \"fix\" didn\'t work this morning. Unfortunately, my husband is going to have to go to the hardware store today to replace it. This is a small appliance that we use every day - it has to be reliable.'),
(6239, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Makes a great cup of coffee, and super fast! This model is super cute and smaller than I had anticipated. This model allows me to brew a cup or a carafe, and that is already my favorite thing about it, since I drink a lot of coffee every day. The only sad part is that this model does not include the carafe, you need to buy it separately, but it shouldn\'t cost more than $20 bucks. I like my coffee strong, and Keurig has an app for that! haha There is a button you can push for strong coffee! I tried the Green Mountain coffee and it tastes great. I specially love that it was ready in less than 2 minutes. So far, I am very pleased with this coffee maker! *I received this Keurig free for testing and reviewing purposes*'),
(6240, 2, 1, 3, '2015-12-26', 'Keep Looking (UPDATE) I feel I should update this review as we didn\'t put it out on the curb but continued to try it out.  So after a week it stopped smoking when using it. Not sure what had to burn off but it\'s now gone, which makes using this much more tolerable.  And no, there was no packing material in there. :) The toast dial is still inconsistent but we\'re learning to be more accepting.  The baking is OK but slow.  Our old B&D would shut off when the door was opened but this one keeps running.  Given the low price and our persistence, I\'ve upgraded my review from \"I hate it\" to \"It\'s okay.\"  The company did contact me to help resolve my issues, which was appreciated.  We probably will replace this with a better model down the line but right now this will do. Our old B&D toaster oven, which we liked, finally died and we purchased this. The larger one seemed too large and we thought this would be comparable to what we had. Wrong! Similar dimensions but not so similar innards. We have tried both toasting and baking several times now and here are our results:  So if you\'re wanting to toast...there\'s a timer that ticks and you have to turn the stiff knob all the way to the right and then back to where you think you might want the setting to be.  There are a range of settings to put the dial between - black, light, and 0. The black setting gives you cremation toast, filling the house with smoke and setting off detectors, the light setting gives you either black toast or nothing at all depending on the phase of the moon and the cosmos at the moment and the 0, well, that actually works.  We are not amused.  If you\'re wanting to bake...the tray that goes under the rack is smaller than the rack so you\'re limited in that respect.  If you want to use your own tray you can\'t because the rack is too high and whatever is in your tray will hit or almost hit the top element. Both toasting and baking, even for brief amounts of time, result in smoke coming out of the sides and knob holes. The only good thing about this is that it\'s not very expensive so we will just put it out on the curb rather than pay to send it back. Oh, and the outer casing is black, which wasn\'t very apparent in the promo.  Good luck and may the toast be with you.'),
(6241, 6, 1, 3, '2015-08-15', 'Judge for yourself You have to judge for yourself. The reviews on this one vary too much. Unless I have the defective version of this toaster I don\'t know how people say they had to put it on the highest setting to toast or it only toasted on one side. On 3 my toast (sliced brioche bread) comes out almost burnt! And it toasts the same on both sides. The toaster itself still has that new appliance smell, but hopefully that goes away soon. I\'ve tried the reheat setting and it worked well. I have not tried a frozen or oversized item yet. When I did the first toast on setting 4, I used the cancel button because I could smell it burning. I don\'t see myself using a setting over 4 because I\'d be afraid the food would catch fire.'),
(6242, 3, 1, 4, '2016-02-12', 'Four Stars Nice but wish timer doesn\'t have to be set to bake'),
(6243, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-26', 'Keeps coffee fresh and hot. Great coffee pot.  Keeps the coffee fresh and hot.  Although, after two months the wire stopper would not seal completely I decided to order a replacement from Amazon because we liked it so much.  Hopefully, the replacement coffee pot will not have any problems.'),
(6244, 9, 1, 2, '2015-10-09', 'Try again First complaint, the Clean button started flashing  just weeks into using. I have cleaned it 3 times, it is absolutely clean-like-New, but that dang button is still flahing. Sometimes it makes gurgling noises like it\'s going to explode. The water reservoir is clear so I have to see water marks and condensation. If I make six cups of coffee, the gauge still reads as full. The light under the dispenser us nice, but that\'s where it stops.'),
(6245, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-22', 'Amazing! Makes a quick pot Amazing! Makes a quick pot, tastes great, actually heats the water up to the proper temperature before running it into the grounds, and the keepwarm setting means my coffee doesn\'t get burnt! =D'),
(6246, 8, 1, 2, '2014-02-05', 'Not to impressed... When I received the product, I ran water threw it several times. It smelled like wires burning.. Had to call the manufactuor and they said dont use it they sent me a new one im still kind of scared to use it :('),
(6247, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-23', 'Uneven toasting. Low quality design of toaster.  Like other reviews said, the bread is unevenly toasted.  See the pictures as attached.'),
(6248, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-18', 'Just good. This device is producing a very flavored coffee. But, I noticed a couple of issues. First of all, there are some random coffee leaks, when it makes it. Then, the new filter system is not so efficient because it makes the grounds in the coffee to be even more noticeable. Also, it needs a lot of water. Its price is decent.'),
(6249, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-14', 'I particularly like the bold feature for slower drip stronger This coffee maker does all it says it will. I particularly like the bold feature for slower drip stronger coffee'),
(6250, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'Don\'t use your oven anymore Awesome..just what I needed'),
(6251, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-06', 'Only thing on my kitchen counter! This Brewer is AMAZING. I\'ve never been a real coffee or tea drinker until Keurig. If you aren\'t a coffe drinker this machine iS still for you. I love the fact that they have Lipton iced tea or Snapple k-cups, even iced coffee. No, this machine isn\'t a cold brew machine but it really doesn\'t matter. The iced k-cups are more strong so when you add ice you still get a great flavor not even watered down! Anyways, I finally had to get one because of all the rave and I am not disappointed one bit. Keurig is a great company and knows how to treat the consumer. Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review! Much appreciation! Everyone needs a Keurig for sure!'),
(6252, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-24', 'Five Stars Great toaster for the money, very even toasting. All the Cuisinart products I\'ve purchased have been great.'),
(6253, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-20', 'Nice oven for small kitchen Little bit small in size than expected. But works well for a smaller kitchen.'),
(6254, 3, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Awesome Product Product works great and fits perfectly in my RV.  I haven\'t had any problems with it baking like it\'s suppose to do.  I\'m glad that I made this purchase'),
(6255, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Five Stars It was a great gift and my mother uses it very day.'),
(6256, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Even if you only drink a little coffee.... We love our Keurig! We are pretty \'light\' coffee/hot beverage drinkers, so we were on the fence about buying one. But we enjoy the speed of brewing single cups as well as carafe packs with our brewer! It has a great option of energy saving too, so the brewer isn\'t constantly \"on\" , but ready momentarily when we need it to be. I highly reccomend this!'),
(6257, 9, 1, 1, '2015-11-03', 'Good for about a week and then it proceeded to leak non-stop. I must be one of the unlucky ones to get a defective, leaky unit. It worked fine for about a week and then one morning it just proceeded to pour coffee without stopping, resulting in the entire contents of the reservoir ending up on my kitchen counter. This is the second defective coffee maker I have bought from Cuisinart. Never again.'),
(6258, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-11', 'Five Stars Luv it.'),
(6259, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-21', 'YES. My husband drinks an obscene amount of coffee everyday and so far - this bad boy has lived up to his expectations. THE GOOD: -It is stylish and sleek. -The water filler being on the back (rather than filling up the coffee pot with water and then pouring it into the back of the device) is extremely simple and convenient. -Having the coffee basket be accessible through the swing open door (rather than the top of the device opening) is also very convenient and prevents you from having to keep the coffee on the edge of the counter to remain wide open so the interior fixtures can dry after making a pot of coffee. -The coffee pot itself has an extra plastic piece along the pouring spout, which has prevented any dripping from the pot to a cup. -Coffee also stays a great temperature when left on without having a burnt taste and also has 3 great brewing options (1-4 cups, regular, and bold). THE BAD (but not really bad unless you\'re not thinking): -The only, only comment I would make is if you are storing this on a counter top that has cabinets over it to pull the coffee maker out from under the cabinets while the coffee is brewing. We haven\'t had any incidents, but are doing this just as a precaution not to have the steam from the brewing mess up the underside of wood of our cabinets. But again, this isn\'t really a \"bad\" as it hasn\'t happened to us. This is definitely an awesome coffee maker - and it only helps that it is a terrific price!'),
(6260, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-04', 'A found treasure We were thrilled to be able to find just what we were looking for in the stores on Amazon!  Perfect in every way.'),
(6261, 9, 1, 2, '2016-09-04', 'Chronic leaking ruins a good coffee maker This Cuisinart makes great coffee and fast but I have to add my review to the chorus of folks out there who complain of leaking. Sometimes the valve doesn\'t want to shut off and you can catch it just dripping. This morning however, I went back into the kitchen and found coffee everywhere and I had to keep pushing the lever upward to get the leaking to stop. This after 11 months since I purchased the unit and no way to get a full refund. For this reason only I would not re-purchase.'),
(6262, 6, 1, 3, '2016-07-20', 'Three Stars Not bad but does not tost evening leaving to top of the toast underdone.'),
(6263, 11, 1, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Very happy with purchase & would recommend. Easy to use, toasts like a dream & looks great too. Was delivered within 24 hours! It arrived so quick I was beyond amazed. My old toaster oven was beginning to smell like plastic burning & the cord was getting very hot. This Black & Decker model has a three-prong cord that does not get hot even after multiple uses within a short period of time. Much safer. The drip pan catches the crumbs but it also has a crumb catcher on the bottom for extra cleaning ease. Definitely would recommend this model for daily use.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(6264, 2, 1, 4, '2015-10-30', 'Love the removable crumb tray Love the removable crumb tray.  The toaster runs a little high in temperature, so you\'ll need to set the timer to a short toasting time.'),
(6265, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-15', 'Good Coffee Maker with stylish design Have used the machine for about a month now. It works great. No problems.'),
(6266, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'Five Stars nice toaster oven, works very well.'),
(6267, 3, 1, 5, '2014-03-17', 'Wonderful product I wanted it because it\'s too hot to use my oven, in my apartment.  It\'s perfect for me. Good quality.'),
(6268, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'So far, very pleased. Just fired this up for my first cups of coffee, so this is an early-days review.  I am replacing a coffee maker that I can\'t remember how old it is, but at least 15 years, so this was a big step.  But so far I am quite pleased with the combination of useful features and reasonable price. What I like/love: I love the lack of handedness.  I\'m a lefty and my old maker required precision pouring into a tiny opening that was meant for a right handed person to use from the rear of the unit.  With the lift out water reservoir, that problem is totally eliminated.  And while the basket button is on the right (no biggie), when the basket is open for use it is equally easy for either hand.  Bravo! And speaking of the reservoir, if one really doesn\'t want to remove it, it can be used in the traditional way by pulling out the unit, lifting the lid and filling it from the carafe or Brita pitcher or whatever.  I found that the water in/coffee out ratio was pretty darn close and I like that. I like the blue light - I can read everything quite easily and since I don\'t sleep in the kitchen, it isn\'t bothersome at night.  I like the setting choices - I tried the regular brew setting this morning and found it a bit weaker than I like, so I\'ll be trying bold tomorrow (even if it is a bit slower).  I like the keep warm choices.  I used maximum while the coffee brewed and once I poured my first (satisfyingly hot) cup, I turned it down to medium. That worked quite well since the last cup (3rd) was as fresh tasting as the first. I like the profile of the unit and the wheels.  The unit rotates easily and it is narrower than my old one, so takes up less counter space.  I really, really like that the carafe is truly dripless - amazing.  I\'m so used to raising the lid in order to pour without drips that I have to keep reminding myself not to do that with this one.  But that leads me to my one discovered con - I don\'t like the fact that the genius carafe means that the last drop never truly comes out.  Drip prevention is thanks to a small shelf just below the spout (on the inside) that has an opening that channels the coffee to the spout and doesn\'t allow it to the sides.  But to get the next to last drops one has to hold the carafe upside down (literally) and then to get the very last drops out, I have to hold it upside down over the sink and shake.  So I guess it\'s a trade off  - no drips but also no last drop in the cup - but a bit of a flaw nonetheless. I\'ll try to remember to check back in a couple of months from now, after the unit has gone through its once a day routine for a while, and we\'ll see how it\'s doing.'),
(6269, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'LOVE LOVE LOVE!! I love the new Keurig 2.0 K250! It is slimmer than the old Keurigs and so much quieter!!! I no longer wake up my whole household in the mornings when making a cup of coffee! This has a touch screen that I love and keeps the machine looking clean!! Also you can purchase a carafe so that you can make a pot of coffee as opposed to 1 cup at a time. I received this product for free to test and review and boy am I glad I did! I can not say enough great things about it. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!!'),
(6270, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-06', 'doesn\'t seem to fit 4 slices of bread unless I ... doesn\'t seem to fit 4 slices of bread unless I smash them together but then its hard to put jelly on a crunched piece of toast'),
(6271, 4, 1, 5, '2015-09-27', 'great buy this toaster oven is awesome! use it multiple times a day and buying another for the office!'),
(6272, 11, 1, 4, '2014-09-27', 'A good oven at a reasonable price. After having a number of toaster ovens that didn\'t do the job, we finally found a good one. It seems to do everything well including making toast.'),
(6273, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-04', 'Great product & very reliable! We love this toaster oven. This is now the second one of this model we have purchased as the first one finally starting having heating issues after many years of use. It does great on toast, but even better at the oven function. We\'ve used it for so many different types of foods and it did well on all of them. There is a newer model, but it\'s larger in size and does not fit in the spot on our counter top as this one does. I would recommend this product and you can\'t beat the price for what it can do.'),
(6274, 6, 1, 1, '2015-07-19', 'Slot too short The slot may be 1 12\" wide but they are too short for anything larger than standard sandwich bread like rye bread. The description needs mention the length of the slot. Returned the toaster.'),
(6275, 1, 1, 1, '2015-10-22', 'Quality Issues I would give this product negative stars if I could. Bought last week and from the first cup, this machine made horrible clunking sounds (like my old, worn-out Keurigs, which I loved), leaked grounds into my cup, and only brewed about half a cup before switching to the \"preheating\" mode, where it stayed until I unplugged it half an hour later. Spoke with Keurig twice - they told me not to use tap water (bottled didn\'t make any difference, though) and that the new technology required more cleaning of the needles (which is why they give you a cleaning attachment - that was kind of my first red flag when I opened the box). It\'s a laugh that they think this machine is in any way capable of brewing a whole carafe (carafe sold separately, of course). They did send me two boxes of pods and offered to replace the machine. But, if this is the new technology, they\'ve got quality issues. I\'m exchanging it for a Mr. Coffee. Oh, and it\'s awful how you can\'t use the refillable cups with the 2.0 tech. Wasteful disappointment.'),
(6276, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-21', 'We LOVED this oven We LOVED this oven, although it has a few minor quirks. The size is great. I can make a whole lasagna in it! I have no issues with any of its cooking functions. The elements do have that shielding which is good and bad. If I put in a very heavy dish (ceramic filled with lasagna), the grate will occasionally jump out of its groove when you aren\'t careful enough sliding it in and crash down. The shield has saved the elements several times. This also means that butter, cheese, crumbs can collect and smoke or catch fire. Just use common sense and you\'ll be fine. We have owned 2 of these. The first lasted several years until one or both top elements burned out. We then ordered the same model (it went stainless steel in the meantime) which lasted almost 2 1/2 years...then one of the top elements burned out. To be fair, we use this oven EVERY DAY, often multiple times a day. It has been a workhorse! The outside does get hot, just don\'t touch or put anything on or against it. The words for the buttons have worn almost completely off, which to me would be a no-brainer kind of thing for the manufacturer to have fixed over the years. As much as I have loved this oven, I might look at one of the other brands just because of the repeated burned out element issue.'),
(6277, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-04', 'Easy to clean Toaster oven in one. Saves a lot of time and this is easy to clean up'),
(6278, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-13', 'Used almost daily. So much easier then to start ... Used almost daily.  So much easier then to start the oven.  Works flawlessly.'),
(6279, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-25', 'Five Stars I love this coffee pot.  Had a POS brew station before this.  This machine is great.'),
(6280, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-11', 'Five Stars Love it.'),
(6281, 5, 1, 3, '2016-05-09', 'It Works I like the way the coffee maker looks, and it works fine, but it is not real durable. The face plate broke off under normal use in less than a few weeks. It appears to be a case of someone tightening down the screws to far when it was being manufactured. It was nothing some supper glued didn\'t fix, but it is still a quality issue. Other than that, I have been mostly happy with the product. It makes a decent cup of coffee, and has basic features.'),
(6282, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-19', 'Five Stars Love this toaster oven!'),
(6283, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-30', 'Great product great service Great product great service.'),
(6284, 12, 1, 1, '2016-04-11', 'One Star so small, you can\'t fit anything inside the oven.'),
(6285, 12, 1, 2, '2014-10-03', 'Oven works great. I used the toaster for the first time ... Oven works great. I used the toaster for the first time yesterday and it will not work. So disappointed!!'),
(6286, 5, 1, 4, '2017-01-22', 'Heating element gave out after 2 years We purchased this coffee maker in October of 2014. The heating element just gave out. I hoped that it would have lasted longer than 2 years, but it is what it is. We used this coffee maker daily the entire time...sometimes making more than one pot a day. Maybe we over worked the darn thing. But with all of that aside, this was a great coffee maker. No other problems with it.'),
(6287, 6, 1, 5, '2016-04-28', 'Nice toaster Finall a toast that works evenly.'),
(6288, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Simple and Elegant, Great Features. Used this to replace our 20 year old toaster.  This is a sturdy, simple, and elegant machine with excellent features, such as the ability to re-warm toast, defrost, and toast bagels as well as other thicker bread slices.'),
(6289, 3, 1, 4, '2015-03-20', 'Great toaster for price but...wording rubs off easily We love out mid sized toaster oven. The convection feature works great and is quiet but most of the printed words on the front have worn off. This makes it impossible for anyone else to use this because only my wife and I know which buttons are which. I like the fact that the heater cover slots get larger as they get farther from the center. As an engineer I know it helps in even heating.'),
(6290, 5, 1, 4, '2014-07-06', 'Four Stars Works well makes great coffee.'),
(6291, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-05', 'Five Stars Worked great, super fast shipping.'),
(6292, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-13', 'Works great! I\'ve baked a chicken Works great! I\'ve baked a chicken, a pork roast, and a cake. I\'ve also toasted toast and bagels. It gets a little hot, but doesn\'t seem like any kind of a hazard. Just remember it gets hot, just like any oven. I haven\'t had an oven in over 2 years. I love this thing.'),
(6293, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'Fancy pants toaster Great toaster! The features seem like some only found on pricier options. Toasts evenly. Attractive (as much as a toaster can be)'),
(6294, 3, 1, 4, '2015-09-25', 'Happy with it. A bit challenging to get all the commands in quickly when you first get it but it works great! This is a replacement for an older Black & Decker model, I am pleased with the upgrade!'),
(6295, 1, 1, 1, '2016-06-20', 'WARNING!  The 2.0 units WILL NOT allow you to use all the pods out there that the 1.0 units will. WARNING.  The 2.0 units WILL NOT allow you to use all the pods out there that the 1.0 units will.  The new units check the K-cup to see if it has markings indicating if it is of an \"approved\" type.  For example most mesh bottom \"cups\" work just fine in the units both 1.0 and 2.0, but 2.0 will not allow them to be used.  They don\'t have the proper markings.  So you have to defeat the scan by clipping on a fake to full the scanner.  I consider that a major defect in the 2.0 series.  It is my decision not Keurig, on what goes in my machine.  I happen to prefer the mesh bottom \"cups\" - you get more aroma when brewed.  I would strongly urge avoiding all 2.0 machines until this Gestapo function is removed.'),
(6296, 2, 1, 2, '2016-09-07', 'Disappointed Very disappointed with this below mediocre toaster.  I will admit I did not get this from Amazon but I did verify that it is the same model number.  I just wanted to warn others.  It is the TO1303SB and I have had it for about 2 years now.  Maybe the new ones have been improved. The 2 problems with this toaster are: 1.  Does not toast even.  Always burns toast in the back.  Seems like that curved part in the back would be a good idea but it looks like it concentrates the heat on the back part of the toast.  And even more uneven is that it burns it more on the bottom than the top. 2.  The toast timer is very vague (bottom knob).  It is hard to get the same amount of time every time.  My last toaster simply had light, medium, and dark and it did the same time each time.  This variable knob just does not work well. The toaster is not all bad.  It looks nice and it has a crumb tray that is easy to clean.'),
(6297, 6, 1, 5, '2014-03-08', 'I owned the four slice model before. I have owned a Cuisinart before.  They are very good and reliable. When replacing my old one, I chose the same model in 2 slice.'),
(6298, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'Excellent coffee maker Excellent coffee maker.  Like that it swivels to get to the water tank and best of all is the swing arm for the coffee grounds.  No more struggling to keep the machine clean as I did with another brand.  Would recommend this to anyone.'),
(6299, 8, 1, 1, '2016-01-28', 'This thing never work, I don\'t have the box ... This thing never work,I don\'t have the box that is why I don\'t return it.Piece of junk!!!!!'),
(6300, 5, 1, 1, '2015-05-03', 'Quit working after 7 months! I bought this coffee maker from Amazon on October 6, 2014. I loved the way it brewed my coffee until only seven (7) months later it quit working. I woke up this morning to brew my daily coffee and the machine was dead even though the electricity works just fine. I tried to plug it into other outlets, but nothing worked. I would expect a gadget like this to work a little longer than seven month. My previous Braun coffee maker lasted 6 years! I would NOT recommend this coffee maker because it is cheaply made judging by how long it lasted.'),
(6301, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-03', 'Breakfast smoothie heaven I use this blender daily to make my breakfast shakes which I take to work in the to-go cup - which is also the blender base. I recommend it only for smoothies and not for anything where you need a food processor. However, I have gifted it to many friends and all rave about it. It is convenient to use and the cup and lid are dishwasher safe - I put in top rack.'),
(6302, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-28', 'Five Stars LOVE THIS COFFEE MAKER.'),
(6303, 2, 1, 4, '2015-03-04', 'I\'m happy with this toaster oven Looks good, works well, vey reasonable price,  only complaint is that it is smaller than the one I had and takes getting use to.'),
(6304, 5, 1, 3, '2016-01-12', 'Could be great, but falls short in durability. I\'ve had this coffee maker for over a year. Here are my thoughts summed up, and why I wouldn\'t buy another: Pro\'s: - Easy to use. I love the removable water reservoir. - Keeps coffee hot without burning or scorching it. - The carafe is nicely designed and doesn\'t leak or spill easily. Con\'s: - The warming plate started to rust after a few months of use. After a year, its over half covered in rust. I\'m now forced to replace. - The writing on the buttons has been wearing off. Luckily, I know what the buttons do by memory. - Hamilton Beach customer service has delayed my issue for a few months, and now my warranty coverage is up. The best they have offered to do is give me 50% off full price on another coffee maker. After shipping, it\'s about the same cost as purchasing from Amazon or a sale price in store. If they could resolve the wear and tear issues, especially the rust, this would be a great buy. Due to those things, I can\'t recommend.'),
(6305, 7, 3, 1, '2015-12-16', 'I bought this because I am not a huge coffee drinker and wanted a single serve maker without paying a fortune. The looks and size of the flex brew were great, however every cup I made had the aroma and taste of pure plastic. I even tried to run straight water through a few times thinking that it would help break it in. The smell and taste made me sick to my stomach. Even when I returned to the store, the lady that opened the box mentioned the smell as it hit her in the face it was so strong. I am not sure what would cause the odor other than it was new? But I would not recommend this coffee maker to anyone. I guess I will need to spend a little more and get a Kerig!'),
(6306, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-07', 'Five Stars Great, so far.'),
(6307, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-14', 'Makes the best cup of coffee I have ever made at home.'),
(6308, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-28', 'Five Stars I am very very happy with this coffee maker. Works great and easy to clean.'),
(6309, 10, 1, 1, '2015-07-29', 'I really wanted to love this. The motor quit on me a week ... I really wanted to love this. The motor quit on me a week after I got it. I put plenty of liquid and did simple jobs but it still gave out. I got a replacement and the second one only lasted a day before not working. I liked the product specs, but with it not working, it\'s useless.'),
(6310, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-25', '... this coffee maker for my office and it is perfect. I brought this coffee maker for my office and it is perfect.'),
(6311, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-30', 'It toasts... Works well.  In hindsight, I wish I would have got it in black or stainless steel.'),
(6312, 7, 3, 3, '2015-10-03', 'It save us money on coffee cause we are not pouring out old coffee. It just takes a while to get several cups of coffee.'),
(6313, 6, 1, 5, '2014-02-21', 'Quality Toaster This was a gift for someone in my family, and they loved it.  I have the 4 slice version, and I have never been disappointed in it.  This toaster can do everything and toast it beautifully.  Yes, I have read customer comments on every toaster about not toasting both sides evenly.  I am getting pretty old and I have NEVER seen a toaster that really can do that! ! ! ??  Let\'s face it - life isn\'t perfectly EVEN!!'),
(6314, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-11', 'Five Stars Awesome toaster and cheap!'),
(6315, 2, 1, 1, '2016-09-10', 'Designed in 1930? You have to set TWO knobs and then a manual timer in order to make toast!  And when the timer runs out, it seems to want to stay on anyway!  What year was it when they designed this thing?  Our old toaster oven that we had for 10 years was way easier to operate, and seemed a lot safer  than this thing.'),
(6316, 9, 1, 4, '2016-12-12', 'Very good,  but not perfect I\'ve had this machine for several weeks.  Some of the things other reviewers have mentioned are spot on : 1. the coffee gauge,  though cute,  is inaccurate.  It does tell you when it is empty,  but the last cup shows it half full. 2.  It is tall,  and must be pulled out to fill with coffee. 3. True,  no carafe to clean,  but you have to clean the coffee reservoir.  I clean it every night after the dishes. 4. The serving light is very cool! My chief complaint is the coffee basket is small.  I only make 8 cups at a time . I tried making more,  but the grounds overflowed and made a huge mess,  depositing into the coffee itself. Maybe I\'m using too much coffee? I do like it dark. Otherwise it\'s a great home drip brewer.  Coffee tastes good,  and is hot.  My husband brass it in the morning at 5:00am, I get mine around 7, and it\'s great.'),
(6317, 5, 1, 3, '2015-03-26', 'does not filter good lots of grounds and sludge in the pot does not filter good lots of grounds and sludge in the pot, advise you to use paper filters, very noisy when percolating, honestly think my old Mr coffee was better'),
(6318, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'I Love My Keurig I bought this brewer at Walmart after price comparing it and finding them to be cheaper. I absolutely love my K200 Brewer. It fits perfectly on the counter and most importantly I get my coffee in a matter of seconds. I highly recommend this model keurig brewer! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(6319, 1, 1, 1, '2016-07-16', 'Keurig are a disaster!! This my 3rd Keurig - two from Costco and last one from Amazon. It\'s not the vendor. Its the Keurig product.  If something doesn\'t work after  6-8 months using daily for( 3) 6 0z cups or 18 ounces @ day, Keurig tells you to disassemble products, descale, clean, use filtered water, fill a bulb, and push 7x.....whatever. If that doesn\'t work SEND coffee maker back to Keurig - at your expense. Keurig will send a___?___ per cent off to purchase another unit. I declined.I still would be losing money. I returned coffee maker #1 to Costco and Costco accepted the unit w/o any questions.  Purchased #3 as a gift.  I refuse to pay $150+ for a product, become a coffee maker technician, return at my expense and receive a coupon to purchase another coffer maker. This does not include the K-Cups (some don\'t work with certain Keurigs), accessories, water filters, etc.  Returning to drip coffee makers. Little can go wrong.'),
(6320, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-19', 'Five Stars Excellent toaster for the money.  Well built & arrived on time.  Cuisinart makes fine products.'),
(6321, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-25', 'Five Stars I especially like the removal water reservoir; makes prep easy.'),
(6322, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-13', 'No style points, but a great coffee-maker none-the-less 5 star coffee-maker with a point deducted for Hamilton Beach not even attempting to create a stylish design. Utilitarian with ho-hum looks. Of all the coffee-makers I have had in my life (Krups, Braun, Mr. Coffee, etc etc) functionally, this one may be the best. No drip carafe, front access to coffee bin, removable water reservoir. All this adds up to a great machine. Just don\'t expect high-style and you\'ll be very satisfied with your new purchase.'),
(6323, 9, 1, 1, '2015-12-29', 'I expected better and this is a serious design flaw Are you kidding me? The cord is only 4 inches long? That\'s not long enough to reach my outlet, which is six inches off the counter.  I just got this today and can\'t see any way to pull the cord out longer. I am NOT purchasing a \"mini\" extension cord to work this thing. I am so frustrated right now. I expected better and this is a serious design flaw. It goes back tomorrow.'),
(6324, 3, 1, 2, '2016-10-26', 'Turned on by itself Worked well for 2 years. Then the temp setting display started to fade but unit was still usable. Final straw was when turned on by itself and temp setting continued to cycled from low to high.'),
(6325, 7, 3, 1, '2016-07-29', 'Very bad, I only used it once.'),
(6326, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-27', 'good value works great and perfect for a fast on the go one serving smoothie!'),
(6327, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-08', 'Five Stars Love it! The carafe option is great.'),
(6328, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-17', 'Got it for a steal! Works great, good deal for the price.'),
(6329, 6, 1, 4, '2016-03-10', 'Four Stars nice toaster, like it'),
(6330, 10, 1, 4, '2016-04-13', 'Blenderific! I love this blender. It\'s perfect for my single serving  Smoothies now that I\'ve been watching what I eat. I am able to take it to work or wherever else I may need to.'),
(6331, 12, 1, 3, '2016-01-20', 'It is just like the one I have had for 18+ years It is just like the one I have had for 18+ years.  This one, however is very cheaply made.  I don\'t expect it to last one year with the amount my family uses a toaster oven.  Good thing it was cheap so I won\'t be sad to have to buy it again next year.'),
(6332, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-17', 'We have one of these toaster ovens and I like it so much We have one of these toaster ovens and I like it so much, I bought one for my son.  No need for two appliances, toaster and oven in one.  Love it.'),
(6333, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-24', 'All in one We got this about a month ago, and so far are very pleased with it.  I really love having the pop up toaster and toaster oven in one.  Both parts work well.'),
(6334, 5, 1, 5, '2016-12-26', 'works great and easy to program Bought this for the holidays, I was going to get one that cost a little less, but after reading the reviews on the others I skipped that one and came across the Hamilton beach coffee maker, the reviews didn\'t let me down, works great and easy to program.'),
(6335, 2, 1, 2, '2016-06-21', 'Really enjoyed this product as long as it worked Really enjoyed this product as long as it worked.  It stopped heating after about 6 months of inconsistent use.'),
(6336, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-22', 'their the best. Joe C You can\'t beat Cuisinart, their the best. Joe C.'),
(6337, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-29', 'Best Toaster EVER! I love love LOVE this toaster!  Browns evenly, and the outside of the toaster stays cool!  Everything I wanted in a toaster!  :-)'),
(6338, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'Great for stroke recovery/mobility issues My mom lost use of her right hand/arm due to a stroke.  So, handling a coffee carafe was a bit challenging for her and worrisome for me thinking she would drop and break it or spill hot coffee on herself.  The Coffee-on-demand is perfect for her.  Easy to clean, keeps the coffee hot without having a burnt taste and she loves that she can fill her coffee cup without worry of breakage/spilling.  So happy we gave this to her for Christmas.  Highly recommended!!!!'),
(6339, 5, 1, 1, '2016-07-20', 'Dont waste your money After only having for 5 months, the entire front face plate (silver plate covering the clock and buttons) has fallen completely off and the basket door is starting to droop on the right side. We have never moved the machine since we set it up (other than utilizing the swivel feature to fill up the water reservoir) so its not from movement. It just sucks that it can\'t be returned or replaced because its an Amazon purchase and past their \"30 day return policy\". Not only am I out for the purchase of this machine, I\'m out again for the search and cost of a new machine.'),
(6340, 5, 1, 4, '2015-04-08', 'great for price So far so good...coffee tastes good and heats up nicely!'),
(6341, 2, 1, 2, '2016-08-09', 'The description is incorrect. On the pictures the oven ... The description is incorrect. On the pictures the oven has 2 sets of rails/grooves providing user with choice. The oven I received has only one so tray is always located too high limiting cooked items height and causing food burning on the top. Returning ...'),
(6342, 9, 1, 3, '2016-01-31', 'Like principal that there is no removable coffee holder needed Like principal that there is no removable coffee holder needed.  Had the previous 14 cup unit, which went bad after about 5 years.  Apparently 14 cup size is no longer make.  Had to settle for the smaller 12 cup design.'),
(6343, 3, 1, 3, '2015-10-26', 'Three Stars Product arrived dented in several areas'),
(6344, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-23', 'We liked the convenience of the ability to brew one cup ... My husband and I were very impressed with the Keurig that we used on a recent visit while staying with friends at their home. We liked the convenience of the ability to brew one cup and not feel like we are wasting coffee with traditional coffee makers when brewing more than needed. Also, the added convenience of having a variety of beverages on hand for those guests who want decaffeinated coffee and/or hot cocoa for the grandkids! We are huge fans of Keurig!'),
(6345, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-25', 'Seem to toast well but a bit hot. We ... Seem to toast well but a bit hot.  We forgot to turn past 10 min. before turning knob to toast so maybe that was why.'),
(6346, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-01', 'Five Stars Makes coffee! Thats all you need it for isn\'t it??'),
(6347, 2, 1, 4, '2016-06-19', 'Four Stars as advertized.'),
(6348, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Best coffee brewing system ever The Keurig 2.0 is amazing! I\'m in love. I had the original Keurig and I loved it, but this one is even better. The design is more compact so there\'s less clutter on my small countertop. I like that you can choose different brewing sizes and that there is the option to brew an entire pot of coffee rather than one cup at a time. This is truly the best coffee brewing system I\'ve ever had. ** I received this product as a sample test and review via influenster.'),
(6349, 10, 1, 3, '2016-01-14', 'I hated it because I would have to make sure the ... Meh.  This product does what\'s advertised, but if you spend a little more money, you can get one that is more effective.  I used this to do very small smoothies at work.  I hated it because I would have to make sure the fruit was all the way thawed and put the liquid to a very low rate because it will overflow. I liked the product, but like I said, I would just buy something a little bit more expensive unless you are just doing juice or yogurt combinations.'),
(6350, 5, 1, 1, '2015-11-03', 'Inexplicable Leaking Within six weeks of purchase, the carafe has started to leak for no reason. Conveniently, I cannot return the coffee maker, the serial number for the carafe is not sold on Amazon, and Hamilton Beach has them on back order. Really wish someone from the seller could help! As Mrs. Lincoln might say, other than the leaking carafe and inability to purchase a replacement or get in touch with anyone, the coffee maker is great.  It looks good, and has all the options that I need.  I did not have any problem keeping coffee at the temperature that I wanted or brewing a nice cup of joe. I also have a chemex and though that coffee might taste a bit better, the convenience of this is great.  I just set it up and walk away.'),
(6351, 4, 1, 4, '2015-05-30', 'but overall a good product. My favorite thing about this toaster oven ... Works as expected, toasts a bit unevenly sometimes, but overall a good product. My favorite thing about this toaster oven is how easy it is to clean!'),
(6352, 6, 1, 1, '2016-04-15', 'Don\'t buy this item. Our second replacement just broke ... Don\'t buy this item.  Our second replacement just broke again.  Won\'t hold bread down.  Major design flaw.'),
(6353, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love this Keurig!!! I bought this particular model having never owned a Keurig before. I wanted the convenience of avoiding the coffee shop everyday and to save money. I had no expectation on what to expect other than I liked the idea of brewing a fresh cup of coffee each time I want one. Also I liked the idea of the variety of flavors. I can change daily the flavor of coffee I drink and I do. I must say that I love my Keurig.  I\'ve had it three weeks. Easy set up and use. It holds a lot of water so I don\'t have to refill it often. It brews quietly and quickly.  Cleaning is easy. Cost of the pods are reasonable. I don\'t see any negatives with this product. I don\'t usually write reviews but I am really impressed with this machine. I would have written this review regardless of the below from Keurig. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(6354, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'Five Stars works just fine, great price'),
(6355, 3, 1, 5, '2015-06-20', 'Five Stars Good Product'),
(6356, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-04', '... researching different coffee makers when I came upon a great review. Was researching different coffee makers when I came upon a great review..so I thought I\'d give it a try..I like the way I push a button and the grounds swing open for me to remove. I lift the back up, fill with water and replace easily. The coffee pot. DOES NOT DRIP!!! Awesome. It did not have a \"plastic\" taste to me but everyone is different. I, for one, am very happy with this coffee maker, including the price!'),
(6357, 7, 3, 3, '2016-07-20', 'Seems difficult to insert the K-cup holder.'),
(6358, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-15', 'Excellent product Well designed and does the job. We were looking for a white toaster to match our kitchen. Slots roomy enough for bagels'),
(6359, 11, 1, 5, '2015-02-19', 'Five Stars Excellent, the product came in as expected.'),
(6360, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-12', 'Love this! This is the second one I\'ve owned. The first one dies after 3 years! I love this little shake maker. I grind ice in it everyday and it\'s just awesome! It\'s been upgraded since my last one and it\'s great! Perfect on the kitchen counter too; doesn\'t take up that much space since I use it everyday. Buy it, you won\'t be disappointed.'),
(6361, 10, 1, 1, '2015-06-09', 'New make is a total waste of money! I have been using same brand old mixer for a while and it works great so I ordered second one to replace...as old one is ready to expire.  I have used this total 3-5 times only.  4th time I was making shake and the bottom blade came off and the liquid was all over the place.  Bottom blending blade was in my hand when I lifted the jar.  Looks like the replacement didn\'t work for more then 5 uses for me.'),
(6362, 5, 1, 4, '2014-01-22', 'Solid product for price Pros: - sleek look, narrow design (if you don\'t mind plastic) - can swivel to access the reservoir more easily - easy access to filter, pop out to fill - easy to use settings (1-4 cups, regular, bold) - can keep pot hot at 3 settings (low, med, high) - programmable - I\'m not a coffee expert, so I actually don\'t know how well it brews.  It\'s tastes better and brews hotter than the old entry-level Keurig I had, which didn\'t do well after a year. - Unlike other reviews, I like the no-drip rim on the pot. Cons (somewhat): - The blue light is noticably bright in my studio apt at night, so I like to unplug it.  It then flashes for me to reset the clock, which I don\'t.  It still lets me make coffee, just slightly annoying. - Coffee shops make it better, which is fine at this price point.'),
(6363, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-22', 'Five Stars Excellent appliance for the price!'),
(6364, 5, 1, 4, '2016-01-19', 'Four Stars Looks good. Works well so far.'),
(6365, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-12', 'As Advertised Love it. Use it daily.'),
(6366, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'Five Stars fits the bill'),
(6367, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-25', 'Toaster oven Just got this !  We are using the toaster in our camper. I can\'t wait to use it instead of firing up the oven. !'),
(6368, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-26', 'Great value. Had a long time toaster oven that started falling apart after it ran its course, and decided on this one because black & decker is a great brand and the price was too good to pass on. So far so good ! It\'s been a few months, so it\'s hard to tell, but I\'m definitely satisfied for now.'),
(6369, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-10', 'DO NOT BUY THIS! The knob was hard to turn on or off. After a few weeks of using only to make toast, I ventured to heat up a piece of pizza. It wouldn\'t turn off. I had to unplug it to make it run off. Then, with the know turned to off  I plugged it back in and it came back on with the know turned to off.  It\'s a piece of crap.  I can\'t carry it to the post office for return so it goes in the dump.  Pricey piece of crap! I thought Black and Decker was a Brand I could rely on but was wrong.  There should be a quality control check on every item before it\'s sold.'),
(6370, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-27', 'Four Stars ok as toaster ovens go'),
(6371, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-11', 'Five Stars Purchased as a gift and he loved it.'),
(6372, 4, 1, 5, '2016-03-03', 'Great buy If you\'re looking for a really good toaster oven thing is the bomb it does everything doesn\'t get over hot on the outside I use mine just fat everyday the price is very reasonable'),
(6373, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-31', 'Five Stars A great basic oven works well..'),
(6374, 11, 1, 4, '2014-03-17', 'It works like all other toasters... _ by turning leftover fried food into a soggy mess. It also simultaneously burns and leaves soft spots on toast.  A marvel of modern technology!'),
(6375, 8, 1, 1, '2016-09-15', 'No Hot coffee ! I didnt expect a product from brand like Black & Decker could be cheap and didn\'t function well ! Simply, this coffeemaker didnt heat the water ! after a min form its done, all what you have is a room temperature coffee !.'),
(6376, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-30', 'Great and easy to use Great and easy to use. It has an issue of burning up too fast though. Can still use it for a good long while, just not too much.'),
(6377, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'The coffee tastes great! We\'d recommend this product to anyone who wants ... As first-timers, we\'re enjoying our new Keurig. The coffee tastes great! We\'d recommend this product to anyone who wants the convenience of making cups, mugs, or carafes in one machine. We\'re very pleased. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(6378, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-15', 'Love this pot Love this pot.  I first saw it at a friends house and decided I needed to get it.  I love the way it\'s so easy to clean and how you put in the water.  No more trying to get the whole pot clean inside when now I can just take it apart for each part that needs cleaning.'),
(6379, 12, 1, 1, '2015-09-11', 'TOO Small The toaster was not deep enough to handle a large bagel and the oven was too small in all dimensions.'),
(6380, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-03', 'Steer away now! Go far away! I say \"screw you\" to the creators of this product and to Hamilton Beach. The blender has one job, to blend. If you want to achieve that, go away. The product is meant to be part blender other part cup to drink from. The sipping hole on the lid is covered with a piece of plastic. This piece of plastic slides over the hole while you\'re blending. This piece of plastic does nothing to keep your liquid inside when you hit the blend button. THE LIQUID FLIES EVERYWHERE. I know it sounds like a joke, but it\'s real. The company must\'ve paid people to write those good reviews.'),
(6381, 1, 1, 3, '2016-02-06', 'Off botton does not work This is a great by except for the fact that the on and off botton displayed on the touch screen does not wort.'),
(6382, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-13', 'Great Toaster!! What a wonderful little toaster!! I am very pleased with it!!'),
(6383, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-01', 'Five Stars Great brewer'),
(6384, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-09', 'Works well after a month - a little hard to set the timer the same each time. Have used it for a month, it toasts evenly. It cleans up easily. The timer setting is not too precise, a little difficult to align the pointer to the exact same place each time.'),
(6385, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-18', 'Our first Keurig & love it. I purchased the K250 and is perfect for me and my wife its the perfect size for 2 people. You have the option of 3 different sizes which is nice if your have friends or family over. I definetly recommend the K250 as you have several options and is compact. Great Product!'),
(6386, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'Several things I like about this product Several things I like about this product.  I can fill the water reservoir with the sink sprayer.  I also like the fact that you can adjust the shut-off time.  The light over the cup when pouring is great because my kitchen is a little dark.  The daily dissemble and clean is quick and easy.  It makes and keeps the coffee hot.  I have found no reason to not love this machine.'),
(6387, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-02', 'MAKES GREAT COFFEE. EASY TO CLEAN MAKES GREAT COFFEE.  EASY TO CLEAN.  COFFEE GRIND FILTER HOLDER SWINGS OUT SO NO GROUNDS SPILL INTO COFFEE MAKER.  WATER RESERVOIR CAN BE REMOVED FOR EASY FILLING AND IS CLEARLY MARKED FOR HOW MANY CUPS NEEDED. THE COFFEE GLASS POT DOES NOT DRIP WHEN POURING.'),
(6388, 6, 1, 4, '2015-01-01', 'Four Stars It has worked fine so far. No complaints.'),
(6389, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-21', 'Five Stars My personal fave from Hamilton Beach, a blender that has appeal and impressiveness packed into one.'),
(6390, 4, 1, 3, '2015-03-27', 'Works just fine, toasts very well and is smaller than a ... Works just fine, toasts very well and is smaller than a lot of toaster ovens.  However:  THE BUZZER WILL DRIVE YOU MAD.  It beeps 5 times when toast is done - it sounds like an alarm going off in the kitchen.'),
(6391, 3, 1, 5, '2014-11-02', 'but are much better than the old on/off temp of my prior one I have had this for a couple months now.  Replaced an old toast convection oven that dies after 6-7 years.  This has worked just as well.  I find the digital controls take a very little getting used to, but are much better than the old on/off temp of my prior one.  Cooks nice and even with or without fan. Only complaint is that I wish I had more control over the fan.  It must be turned on from the beginning.  You can\'t just hit the fan button when you want to turn it off and on.  Seems like a simple feature that they disabled for some reason.'),
(6392, 6, 1, 3, '2015-07-29', 'NOTHING \"COMPACT\" ABOUT THIS (BAGEL) TOASTER IN SHORT-- If you want a acceptable big bagel toaster, you\'ve found it.  If you want a compact sliced-bread toaster, I\'d keep looking. ITS BIG > There is nothing compact about this 2-slice toaster.  From the photo, It looks (to me) as though it measures about 5\" x 6\" x 8\", which would be reasonable for a 2-slice \"compact\" toaster.  In fact it measures 6.5\" x 7\" x 11\"---larger than the \"standard\" toaster it is replacing.  That may not matter to you.  But for those of us with tiny kitchens, every inch counts. OTHER ISSUES > The widest bread slices it accommodates is a little over 5\" wide---the bread I purchase is usually larger. > The MINIMUM opening of the CPT-122 is 3/4\" and it opens up to 1 1/4\".  So, it doesn\'t do well with thin-sliced bread, \"pop-tarts\" etc > It toasts very unevenly.  The side toward the outside is barely toasted compared to the inside side.  That\'s great for bagels, but very poor for sliced bread. >->  So, insert bagels with the cut side on the inside side. That way, the outside will only be lightly warmed.  There is no point in using the bagel setting, because it doesn\'t do anything. MY APOLOGIES I\'m very critical when other reviewers claim that \"it was smaller than I expected\" or \"it was larger than I expected\", because it\'s stupid to buy a (size-important) product without checking measurements.  The caveat is that Amazon often cites the measurements of the retail box rather than the actual product measurements.  I thought that the quoted measurements for the CPT-122 were for the retail box.'),
(6393, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-06', '... a short time but it seems to be a good oven. I\'ve only had it a short time but it seems to be a good oven.....as advertised.'),
(6394, 7, 3, 4, '2015-01-05', 'This machine brews a good, quality, hot cup of coffee and will use any brand of the original series K-Cups, name brand or generic. This unit does not contain a water reservoir so can be on the messy side until you grow accustomed to it. The cup receptacle unit is manual which results in a noisier brew than the higher end machines, but the end result is the same. It also comes with a basket for regular ground coffee. The unit is not bulky and has an attractive design. Overall I am pleased with my purchase; I think it\'s a great value for the price and would recommend one to a friend as an affordable alternative to pricier models.'),
(6395, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-04', 'It is working fine. The icons are a bit hard to read It is working fine.  The icons are a bit hard to read, but it does the job.'),
(6396, 2, 1, 4, '2015-04-10', 'I kept the enamel baking tray from the toaster oven that just died - this one comes with a super lightweight cheapy aluminum thi For those wondering about toast, it works perfectly.  I kept the enamel baking tray from the toaster oven that just died - this one comes with a super lightweight cheapy aluminum thing. The dials are a bit of a hassle as the writing and icons are so teeny it is hard to see, especially when the toaster isn\'t at eye level which it usually isn\'t!  But I\'m sure once I am familiar with them it will be fine. Has a slide out tray but it has to til to come out which means you will dump all your crumbs back into the toaster.  Very short cord.'),
(6397, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-21', 'Very nice. The size and performance is very good Very nice.  The size and performance is very good.'),
(6398, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'black and decker toaster-oven excellent-'),
(6399, 12, 1, 1, '2014-11-15', 'unfortunately like so much of what we see today This does not in any way compare with the Hamilton Beach Oven I have had for years.  In fact I  wanted to return it, but did not keep the box. The oven space is so small, it\'s rediculous.  The toast jumps out of the toaster.  All in all, I find the item to be of cheap, inferior quality, unfortunately like so much of what we see today.  It seemed to be such a job to return it.  OK, that\'s it.'),
(6400, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-29', 'Good for Smoothies! Makes great individual smoothies.  Does not come apart for cleaning.  I put detergent and hot water in and run it.  Will use it a lot in warmer weather.'),
(6401, 11, 1, 4, '2014-10-07', 'and my coworkers like it. Very handy little toaster oven. Bought it for our office, and my coworkers like it.'),
(6402, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-27', 'Just the right size Perfect toasting and warming feature. The oven is a good size. Not a whole lot bigger than a double toaster but more useful than that. Can use for small things that you don\'t want to warm your whole oven for like frozen fries, garlic toast etc.'),
(6403, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-17', 'Five Stars It\'s perfect.'),
(6404, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-17', 'Best coffee maker I\'ve ever had Best coffee maker I\'ve ever had! Brews fast and hot, the regular setting is perfect brew strength for me. I like that the reservoir removes for filling at the sink, not spilling water on my counters anymore. Program setting is great too. Should have replaced my old coffee maker with this one months ago!'),
(6405, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-15', 'easy to use and cleans up easily Cheap, easy to use and cleans up easily.  I\'ve used it quite a bit since it arrived.'),
(6406, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Five Stars Great!.'),
(6407, 10, 1, 2, '2015-01-01', 'Spend your money on an immersion blender. I was trying to save some money by getting this rather than a magic bullet. I should have gotten an immersion blender. The blades are so short that chunks of things simply stay under them rather than get blended. The only value is for things that are totally liquid to begin with. Bread crumbs, smoothies, and coffee beans are not even a possibility.'),
(6408, 6, 1, 2, '2015-08-30', 'Better than using the oven broiler to toast 2 slices of bread Looks nice and  is compact but only toasts well on the side facing the elements between the slots, which  is fine for bagels or English muffins, but not typical bread slices. I don\'t see any difference between the various settings  (bagel, defrost, etc.) but the toasting time numbers do seem to work. I always have to start on a lower number and then flip the toast to do again, watching carefully so it doesn\'t burn. If we ate more toast I would have returned it to the department store where I bought it on sale about 8 months ago. It\'s too late to now but I will get a new one in a different brand before we have more overnight guests.'),
(6409, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-03', 'Small, but great price! Great toaster... Wish it was a bit bigger. But the price was right for the size.'),
(6410, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-16', 'Just right! Great little toaster at a reasonable price!'),
(6411, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-02', 'If It Wasn\'t For The Proprietary K-Cup Nonsense This Would Be A 5 Star Brewer I love the convince & ease of use of this machine but I am extremely disappointed in the very limited variety of K-Cups the 2.0 & later will accept.  Keurig made it so inconvenient that their own older style K-Cups will not work in this machine.  Thankfully there is a way around their desire to monopolize the K-Cup industry.  First, if you have some K-Cups that are 2.0 compliant, save the lid & put it over your non compliant K-Cup & then you can use your non approved K-Cup.  You can also buy special stickers (I haven\'t tried this).  Last you can order a re-usable brewer cup to brew your own loose coffees & teas.  I ordered the & can happily tell you that it works perfectly.  I love it! Once you get past the K-Cup situation, the Keurig really is fantastic for it\'s convenience, ease of use, & space saving abilities.  The touch screen is very sensitive, even with wet fingers.  I love having one machine for coffee, tea & cocoa.  This means no more separate machines to satisfy everyone\'s tastes.  This frees up precious counter space in my teeny tiny kitchen, so this is a big deal in my household.  You can even purchase that the brewer sits on, saving even more space. Overall (aside from the proprietary nonsense with the cups) the whole family loves this machine.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(6412, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-24', 'I Like This Keurig Brewing System This Keurig 2.0 Brewing System has replaced the B70 we used for about two years. We have passed that one on to our son. I like the appearance of this one much better; it\'s not bulky, but compact and looks nice on the counter. Instead of buttons to choose cup size, there is a 2 inch black and white touch display. I love this feature. And there is also a strength control setting and a Hot Cocoa/Other setting. My husband drinks one cup of coffee a day, using the Folgers K-Cup with the Keurig Brewed seal. I drink two, sometimes three cups of tea, using Twining Green Tea and Twining Chai Black Tea K-Cup with the Keurig Brewed Seal. There are over 500+ different varieties, from 75 brands - way more than enough to choose from if we want a change. This system came with three coffee K-Cups and a Hot Cocoa K-Cup. Also included was one water filter handle and two charcoal filters and one descaling solution. Keurig Carafe is sold separately. After filling 40oz reservoir below the MAX FILL line and above the MIN FILL line, placing cup on drip tray and pressing power button on touch screen: Welcome Preheating Lift to Begin (place K-Cup pod in holder, lower handle, and select brew size- 4,6,8 or 10oz) Press Brew Button Enjoy *The system will immediately begin preheating for next cup. Press power button for a second or two turn off. *There is an instruction manual (English, French & Spanish) *Also available, although we\'ll probably never use:'),
(6413, 5, 1, 2, '2015-04-22', 'Three Stars This coffe maker is not a good one at all I been use this for awhile and the temp of the high is 192 degree and doesn\'t get hot at all. Every time I make coffee it warm and taste terrrible. I would advise for some one who interested in the brand to look some  where else this machine is not good at all.'),
(6414, 12, 1, 5, '2014-09-06', 'Five Stars Product works well!'),
(6415, 9, 1, 5, '2016-04-25', 'My lifesaver This is a lifesaver for me! I use it to make my coffee everyday in the morning before I head off. It\'s incredibly easy to clean; you literally just open the top and pop out the reservoir and clean as needed. It also doesn\'t take long to make coffee and the programmed brew feature is something I love. I can set it to start making coffee at a certain time automatically so I don\'t have to do it. This gives me extra time to sleep as well as not forgetting to make my coffee in the morning.'),
(6416, 4, 1, 2, '2015-09-28', 'It will burn more than your toast! Worked great until the element cracked and created a hotspot.  I was waiting for it to burn our house down, but it died.  We got 3 years out of it though.  The defect was first visible about 2 years into owning it.  Read the other reviews here and look at the questions.  Evidently, it\'s a thing.  But for ~$70 I guess that\'s what you get.'),
(6417, 7, 3, 5, '2016-02-21', 'Works great. I especially like being able to use pods, softpods or loose coffee.'),
(6418, 11, 1, 1, '2014-06-07', 'Disappointed I bought this in November 2013 and have used it maybe a dozen times. Was never quite able to figure the settings right so my muffins would not burn, and frequently smoke came out the top of the door. But today I plugged it in and nothing. I tried other sockets, but nothing. Not a lot of dollars invested, but I did think it would last much longer like my old one.'),
(6419, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-21', 'I love this coffee maker I love this coffee maker! It  replaced a Cuisinart one that cost twice as much and that I never liked as well as this one. It is very easy to fill and see how much water is in it. It also has the setting for bold or strong coffee which I love. Highly recommend!'),
(6420, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-22', 'Five Stars Best coffee maker yet!!.'),
(6421, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-05', 'Great coffee maker for the price This coffee maker is easy to use, not too many parts to wash and is very efficient for the price.  Wanted to use whole bean so bought a separate coffee grinder.  Had the Cuisinart Grind and Brew that worked okay, but it had too many parts to clean and the coffee wasn\'t any better than the lower priced Hamilton Beach.'),
(6422, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-12', 'You\'ll be glad you bought this one :) This is a great coffee maker. I bought it because of other reviewers\' comments, and very happy that I did. Best features for me are the removable water reservoir, swing out coffee / filter, automatic start, automatic shutoff, adjustable heater temp (so coffee drunk after 2 hours on warm doesn\'t taste burnt!).  You will be glad you picked this one. I also have a Hamilton Beach toaster oven and electric can opener that work great.'),
(6423, 8, 1, 2, '2016-01-18', 'INCOMPLETE. CUTE, MAKES GOOD COFFEE  BUT THE COMPANY DIDNT INCLUDE ANY FILTERS NOR ANY DIRECTONS ABOUT THE SIZE OF THE FILTER TO BUY. NOT GOOD BLACK AND DECKER. . IT ISNT WORTH SENDING BACK, BUT I SURE FEEL LIKE I BOUGHT 1/2 A PRODUCT.'),
(6424, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-06', 'Four Stars Small blender works pretty well. Not for big jobs'),
(6425, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'Five Stars Great coffemaker. Removable water resrevoir makes it easy to fill. Lots of nice features. Good value for the price.'),
(6426, 7, 3, 1, '2015-01-13', 'I find that this coffee maker does not preform as stated. I never get a full cup of coffee, even if I add additional water. Have to brew twice to get a full cup. Makes terrible noise\'s while brewing. Although it is a great concept to be able to brew k cups and regular coffee, does not preform as I thought it would.'),
(6427, 9, 1, 3, '2016-07-26', 'Three Stars Nice quality.'),
(6428, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-14', 'Five Stars Best thing to happen to me in a while... so easy to use, quick, fast, and convenient.'),
(6429, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-28', 'and I like the drinking vessel more than my OSTER that costs ... Not a strong blade - you have to keep letting the spinach leaves fall to the bottom by pulsing the button. But it\'s more attractive, and I like the drinking vessel more than my OSTER that costs twice as much. For the price, I have them shipped to hotel rooms whenever I travel and give them to the housekeeper when I leave as a tip.'),
(6430, 2, 1, 2, '2015-07-21', 'Fire hazard I had this toaster for 6 weeks and there was a fire inside, but nothing had spilled on the heating element. After that, it wouldn\'t shut off and became a fire hazard. The timer wasn\'t really the clearest as well. Unfortunately I was past the return policy, so it felt like a complete waste of money.'),
(6431, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-14', 'Five Stars my wife likes it'),
(6432, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-29', 'Five Stars EXCELENTE'),
(6433, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Great Product ! ! ! Love this little toaster ! ! I do Frosted Pop Tarts on the inside where they don\'t get broken. My Tyson Chicken comes out tender and juicy. Best Frozen Chicken Breast Strips I\'ve ever had. They absolutely melt in your mouth. No need for dipping sauses. Sometimes I do use a little ketchup. Does Ball Park frozen burgers to perfection. Easily controled temperature. Haven\'t even used the toaster function yet. Guess I\'ll have to put bagels and cream cheese on my shopping list.'),
(6434, 5, 1, 2, '2015-08-31', 'buy something else have had it for a couple of months now. takes forever to brew 4 cups. sometimes not very hot.'),
(6435, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-07', 'I thought this was a good purchase Also gave this to my daughter and family.  They used it. I hope they like it.  Looked pretty neat to me'),
(6436, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-20', 'SERIOUS SAFETY ISSUES I burned my hand when closing this thing, and so did my wife. There is a black metal strip behind the plastic door handle that gets incredibly hot and is very easy to touch, especially when closing the door. I measured the temperature, it was 260 degrees Farenheit. Since the strip is the same color as the handle it is easy to think it is part of the handle. In addition, it is too easy to leave this thing ON when you are done with it. To turn off the toaster, you turn the timer knob to the left until it \"dings\" if you turn a tiny bit too far, you will leave the unit in the \"permanently ON\" mode.'),
(6437, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-14', 'Really like this for my counter but one slight negative Really like this for my counter but one slight negative... Can\'t turn it sideways and be able to control the toast darkness. So it has to face forward. Nice product.'),
(6438, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-12', 'Got this for my husbands birthday. It arrived today ... Got this for my husbands birthday. It arrived today and he opened it early. He was so excited and it lived up to the hype. He loves it. It\'s convenient and he said the instructions and the way it was set up was idiot proof.'),
(6439, 12, 1, 5, '2016-05-30', 'Five Stars Love it!!'),
(6440, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-04', 'Is very easy to use for my kids and very easy to ... We are loving our new toaster oven ! Is very easy to use for my kids and very easy to clean. I haven\'t use to cook anything but as far as baking a small frozen pizza, toasting bread and making a sandwich and warming up everything is working great . We are very happy with a toaster oven.'),
(6441, 6, 1, 2, '2016-07-25', 'up in smoke! I had a Cuisinart toaster for 10 years. It was great--substantial in weight and toasted evenly. However, one day it just stopped toasting. So I ordered another Cuisinart.  When this version came, it was lightweight and looked really cheap. From Day One, it has toasted unevenly. I had to keep the dial on the lowest number possible, in order to keep from burning the toast. Today--after only 5 months of use--it has crashed.  I caution everyone who is considering a purchase of a Cuisinart toaster to look for some other brand. Their current products aren\'t made at the same standard as previous ones.'),
(6442, 2, 1, 1, '2015-03-05', 'Waste of time and money I have been through 2 of these in 2 months - both units have worked fine for 2 weeks, then they work sporadically and by the end of the month not at all. I do not recommend this toaster. Update: 3 units in less than a year. Same issue with each unit - heating elements stopped working.'),
(6443, 5, 1, 2, '2016-07-19', 'Faceplate fell off after 2 weeks, and was clearly broken. Brewed fine, but as others have complained, the faceplate around the buttons fell off in a couple weeks. And after looking at the back of it, it clearly had broken pieces that were supposed to hold it in...but it had never been knocked against anything, or dropped or something...there\'s no reason the plastic should have been broken on a brand new product.'),
(6444, 7, 3, 2, '2015-01-25', 'When you pour a cup of water in the reservoir in the top, it drips off the cup and makes a mess. I\'m returning it for a different model. The coffee it made was good, however.'),
(6445, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-27', 'so good! This is our second one.  So far, so good!'),
(6446, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-27', 'Don\'t buy, 2 were defective I bought this as a Christmas gift for my parents. They tried it and found that it only toasted on one side. They contacted Cuisinart and were told it was defective. We advised Amazon and with their amazing customer service they replaced it. Unfortunately the replacemen talso has the same defect and only toasts on one side. The positive reviews make it sound like a great product, but sense to have the same defect we will not try a third one.'),
(6447, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Five Stars Works great - easy to use.'),
(6448, 7, 3, 4, '2016-11-22', 'Love it and cleans easy!'),
(6449, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-05', 'Easy to operate for whole family Right size for my counter space. Easy to operate for whole family.'),
(6450, 2, 1, 2, '2016-08-05', 'Too complicated.... I have learned but ... Too  complicated.... I have learned but it is not user friendly.  Sorry.'),
(6451, 5, 1, 2, '2014-12-26', 'VERY disappointed.. I purchased this coffemaker on 11/21/14...had I for 7 days and it came down one morning at 4 a.m. and it was dead...it had QUIT WORKING!!! Luckily I bought the Canopy Protection Plan with it, but when I called them they sd I had to call Hamilton Beach because it was within their warranty. Called them and told them that it had DIED and after taking pictures and sending a copy of my receipt they send me another one. If this one dies I am going to ask for a refund!!! Thankfully I had saved my old Mr Coffee coffee pot that was 3 years old!!! VERY disappointed....'),
(6452, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-23', 'Stop looking and buy this one, works great, flawless design. Not sure why I\'m writing a review of an item that already has so many positive reviews... Well made and very well designed. I like how the water pitcher in the back goes in and out flawlessly and the front door swings open for super easy access to the filter assembly part. Unit is easy to clean. Normally I use a pour-over method for making coffee but bought this for my coffee club that meets once a week. The capacity is a few more cups than most units and tastes as good as my pour-over coffee. It has a bold setting which I believe just pours the water more slow over the coffee grinds, nice feature. I\'m a very picky shopper and do way too much research finding the one I like most, if you want to save time yourself just buy this one, works great!'),
(6453, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-26', 'Cracked after a month. Loved it while it worked. After a month or two it decides to crack while in use. Save your money and buy elsewhere.'),
(6454, 8, 1, 4, '2016-10-01', 'So far no complain. Good work. No plastic smell.'),
(6455, 8, 1, 1, '2015-12-29', 'One Star not safety'),
(6456, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-16', 'price was right. size was right, did toast ... price was right. size was right, did toast well and didn\'t have any unwanted bells and whistles.  Just what I wanted and needed, and it was delivered to my door.  Enough said'),
(6457, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-12', 'Five Stars Very nice toaster oven'),
(6458, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-25', 'Excellent toaster for the money Excellent toaster for the money.  I actually bought a more expensive Cuisinart one but it was too large.  I have a dedicated space for one and the Black and Decker fit perfectly.  I have been very happy with it and it works perfectly.  Honestly, I see no need for a more expensive one.  This one does the trick!'),
(6459, 5, 1, 1, '2015-12-06', 'REJECT PURCHASE HB COFFEE MACHINE DUE TO SERIOUS EQUIPMENT/CUSTOMER SVC REVIEWS I have this on my cart, ready to purchase it, but decided to decline after reading the reviews issue towards short life of this product and following customer svc response. What makes a company great, even in the long term is \"A Wow Experience\" When that is lost, in time profits will diminish. Off to another brand coffee machine hunt. I\'m so grateful that we now have the teamwork, and technology to buy wisely within the consumer arena. For better or worse review, I thank each and every one of you.'),
(6460, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-20', 'Not happy with it Defiantly not worth the $15! I wasn\'t even using it for 5 minutes...just put berries, a couple ice cubes, and milk in and the device got so hot I had to let go. Wouldn\'t blend my ice cubes or even my berries which were thawed. Not happy with it..at all.'),
(6461, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Great cup of coffee It does a great job brewing and keeping coffee warm without that \"burned\" taste that carafes produce.  However, I must admit that I liked the look of its predecessor more.'),
(6462, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-10', 'One Star Bottom of the blender cup chopped after a few uses'),
(6463, 5, 1, 4, '2014-01-16', 'Great coffee! This is really nice!  I love the look. I give only 4 stars because it shuts off after 2 hours instead of 3-4 and it seems to take a while to brew. But everything else is great.'),
(6464, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-27', 'Four Stars Makes great coffee, easy fill for water and carafe lip helps stop spills when over pouring'),
(6465, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-11', 'One Star Very small and returned!'),
(6466, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Great product Great product. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(6467, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'I enjoy the convenience of having a hot cup of coffee I have not owned a home brewing system until now. I enjoy the convenience of having a hot cup of coffee, cocoa, tea, or just water. While I wish the water tank could hold more water, I like that it does not take up much space on my kitchen counter top. You can also choose a color to match your style. I chose black. Thanks, Keuring, for the free pods for this review.'),
(6468, 10, 1, 5, '2015-06-09', 'Five Stars Perfect for those on the go moms or college students, Quality built and looks amazing. Shipping was fast to!'),
(6469, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-02', 'Beautiful, easy to use machine. Nicer than I expected. Makes great coffee for a drop in this range. I own an automatic espresso machine. I really like coffee, strong coffee. Not everyone that visits appreciates my cafe Americano and we get a lot of visitors, so I decided to get a standard drip machine for when we had company. This is a straight forward machine. I didn\'t need a manual to set it up or get it going. It has a great  look to it.  In fact we use it more than we thought we would.'),
(6470, 8, 1, 5, '2014-09-15', 'Great value! This unit is a great Great value! This unit is a great, no frills, basic coffeemaker.  I wasn\'t expecting much, but I get surprisingly very good coffee from it (I use two tablespoons of ground coffee per cup).  It has a window on the reservoir with fill lines so you can see if you have the right amount of water. The pot is attractive and ergonomically well designed with an ample spout.'),
(6471, 2, 1, 4, '2015-04-30', 'Not easy to read the indicators Print is too small.  Not easy to read the indicators.'),
(6472, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-31', '... bought this for my boyfriend and he couldn\'t be happier! It heats up very fast and cooks very ... I bought this for my boyfriend and he couldn\'t be happier! It heats up very fast and cooks very well.'),
(6473, 5, 1, 3, '2014-04-22', 'Slow We only have the one machine so maybe ours is exceptional but it takes 12-14 minutes to brew a 10 cup pot of coffee.  It also requires a lot more coffee to get the same strength that I was used to.  We had Braun units that took cone shaped filters so perhaps that had something to do with it.  They were super fast (5-6 minutes for a full pot) and definitely required less coffee.  The Brauns were made in Germany and achieved a bit of \"cult like\" status, we had to buy them used on Ebay, but after a couple years they were getting tired so we tried this machine.  It is well made, convenient, and IMO far better than the Mr. Coffee machines.  The best part is the large bright display that makes seeing and setting the time very easy compared to other machines.  The slow brew time is not a problem if you are setting it to go off the next morning, just allow plenty of time.  But if you want a pot right now it is tedious to wait.  I have no idea why it takes so much coffee to achieve a normal brew strength, but we now use the \"bold\" setting and about 25% more coffee than we used to.  I would not buy this machine again but it\'s not a bad choice, perhaps ours was not functioning as well as it should have.'),
(6474, 4, 1, 5, '2016-09-30', 'Works well... use it everyday! Works well ... use it everyday! Bought another one for my daughter.'),
(6475, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-13', 'Toast is either not done or burnt. It\'s impossible!!! It either doesn\'t toast the bread or it burns it. There so little space for toast ... probably a half inch or less between not done and burnt and the dial is hard to turn, no good markings there.. so it\'s basically impossible to consistently get a nice toast unless you sit in front of it and catch it before it burns, which on a regular morning is an impossible feat. Baking is fine, toasting is not. Anyway, about to throw this thing in the dumpster after the last few months of total frustration with it.'),
(6476, 3, 1, 4, '2015-05-27', 'Four Stars LOVE IT!'),
(6477, 6, 1, 5, '2015-12-30', 'Great! Exactly what we wanted. Used it for the first time today on a bagel- perfectly toasted!'),
(6478, 11, 1, 1, '2015-01-19', 'Poorly Designed and Engineered This is an update now that I\'ve been using this product for well over a year. I know that products and their designs change, but the idiosyncrasies of the Black and Decker taster over outweigh its usefulness. The product is oddly engineered with a crumb tray that blocks the heat element on the bottom when you want to toast bread which is the primary use, I would think, of a crumb tray. The manual timer is irritating which is small potatoes compared to the fact that both upper and lower heating elements run any time the oven is in use. I would think at a minimum that a toggle switch would be useful so that you could only broil from the top, bake from the bottom or use both. I miss my old Black and Decker.'),
(6479, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-12', 'Great product All that I expected. Plan to use it to the max.'),
(6480, 5, 1, 5, '2015-12-21', 'Five Stars Excellent'),
(6481, 4, 1, 3, '2016-03-25', 'Works great, wish it didn\'t have a load annoying multi beeping signal when done This toaster oven works well, my biggest complaint...the load annoying beeping when done toasting. I make breakfast early in the morning while my wife and infant daughter are still asleep and it wakes them sometimes. No way to turn it off.'),
(6482, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-12', 'Tottally worth the 10$ I paid for it. It\'s portable and effective. I tottaly recommend this item. I was worry about if it can crush ice and iced fruit but it has no problem with that. I maked smoothies with 5 block of ices, 2 bananas and sugar. It has never stuck or suddenly stop because of the hard items on it. Tottally worth the 10$ I paid for it. It\'s portable and effective.'),
(6483, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-26', 'Satisfied b its value and performance! Satisfied because of its value! The blender does the job fine and it is easy to operate unlike other blenders that you have to push so many buttons just to have it functioning.'),
(6484, 5, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', 'Best coffee maker I\'ve owned Best coffee maker I\'ve owned! My favorite part is how you fill the water. It does what it\'s supposed to do.'),
(6485, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-07', 'Works reall well. Love it, reliable, multiple options and yet simple enough. Has plenty of room inside. Could handle up to 6 slices of bread if you have smaller size sliced bread. Pretty powerful too.'),
(6486, 10, 1, 3, '2016-03-25', 'Not ideal for blending ice, but otherwise fine Works well for basic blending but not for blending ice for smoothies.'),
(6487, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'I didn\'t know. I love my new Keurig, and I love the variety of tea\'s and coffee that are available! Thank you Keurig for the free pods!'),
(6488, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-25', 'Five Stars I got what I wanted. No problem.'),
(6489, 2, 1, 3, '2015-09-08', 'It doesn\'t bake anything very well and it toasts rather slowly but it does the basic job which is fine. It\'s mediocre. I guess you get what you pay for. It doesn\'t bake anything very well and it toasts rather slowly but it does the basic job which is fine.'),
(6490, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-19', 'Five Stars Loved it enough to buy it again.'),
(6491, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-15', 'No messy pot to spill or deal with I love this coffee maker it\'s easy to clean and easy to use. It looks great and there is no messy or ugly pot to deal with.'),
(6492, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-09', 'Five Stars Looks and works great!!!!.'),
(6493, 1, 1, 4, '2015-09-21', 'It\'s Purple! there are a few things that kinda drive me nuts about this machine. it is all plastic. my coffee cup is always sticking to the top of the catch basin, silly little things like that. filling it all the time doesn\'t bother me at all, because even when i had a larger reservoir i would fill it every 2 cups, so i do the same w/ this one, although I think you can get 4 / 10 oz cups from it. What i love about it is that you can make a *strong* cup o coffee. it is a bit slower than my other machine, but i see this as a good thing, I can do the 10 extra *but first i gotta do this* while i am waiting for my cup to be created. And most of all, the most important feature...it is PURPLE! now, you can never go wrong when something is purple! =) sue'),
(6494, 5, 1, 1, '2016-07-25', 'Fell apart! Have had it for just over a month- and the face plate surrounding the clock fell off. Too late to return, would love for someone to step up and make this right!.'),
(6495, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-08', 'It is easy to use This toaster oven has met and exceeded my expectations. It is easy to use, works well and I\'m extremely satisfied with it. It is also not too big for my counter-top and looks great. I was given a pricier alternative as a gift which I promptly returned and ordered this one.'),
(6496, 9, 1, 4, '2015-08-23', 'Makes great coffee and overall a good fit for me I really like this coffee maker except for 2 very minor things.  1)  I can\'t dump freshly ground coffee straight from the grinder if I am using a paper filter in additional to the filter basket, which is my preference  2)  Takes a little more time to empty the reservoir if didn\'t drink all that was made in comparison than just dumping a pot.  Other than these little things, it works very well for me and makes great coffee!.'),
(6497, 5, 1, 1, '2016-07-09', '2 week life span & Fire hazard This worked for 2 weeks. Like many other reviews the face plate was trying to pop off. One morning my husband said it got so hot it nearly burned his hand. After 2 weeks it just stopped, on a Monday morning none the less. Piece of junk, I should\'ve listened to the other reviews instead of crossing my fingers that I\'d get one of the few that actually work. I don\'t have time to hassle with packaging things back up & mailing them back so I just chalked it up to a lesson learned. Very disappointing.'),
(6498, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Five Stars very satisfied'),
(6499, 5, 1, 1, '2015-10-15', 'Replacing it due to rust on the heating plate - less than a year old! The heating plate started corroding almost immediately after the first use.  Now, the plate is rusted, there is rusty gunk all over the bottom of the carafe and the front of the machine, and the carafe does not slide easily into the chamber because of the rust.  Really disappointed, because otherwise we love the features and how well it has worked.  I guess we got a dud that wasn\'t finished properly.  I can\'t stand looking at the rust any longer, so I\'m ordering a new one, but a different brand.'),
(6500, 8, 1, 5, '2014-09-29', 'Excellent Coffee Maker! If you want a no frills but reliable coffee maker, look no further. I\'ve owned one previously but I cracked the carafe. I bought another one cup version but bought this one again mainly because it is ridiculously simple to use and the coffee is hot. I would highly recommend this coffee maker to anyone who needs a basic coffee maker and doesn\'t want to pay a designer price.'),
(6501, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-23', 'Just my cup of tea.....I mean coffee. I love the detachable water reservoir. The brew time seems faster than average and I use the \"Bold\" setting. The lip on the carafe does not dribble at all and I love that too. The slim compact design fits nicely on my counter top. It has very simple user friendly controls. Bottom line:  I made a very good choice buying this coffee maker and I highly recommend it.'),
(6502, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Five Stars Great! Hamilton Beach Blender - For make smoothies and shake using frozen fruit or fresh fruit in the mixture. Not use Ice cubes and hard ice cubes for Plastic Jar crack break.make be carefully read to instructions book.'),
(6503, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-02', 'Five Stars I\' m happy with my purchase.'),
(6504, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-10', 'We love everything about this coffee maker We love everything about this coffee maker!!  One feature we especially like is the light that comes on as you fill a cup ~ very handy to see as the coffee dispenses into a dark cup - you don\'t overfill!!.'),
(6505, 6, 1, 4, '2014-12-04', 'Cuisinart CPT-122 Compact Toaster I\'m really happy with the toaster, it works really well. It was nice getting a good deal on the dresser, there was an online coupon on Amazon for it the day I ordered. So far its doing its job no problem. The reheat button on it works great as well as the other funcfor methe only downside for me is that beyond the setting of three or four it literally comes out black toast. To me they should we do the settings to only include the numbers 1 to 4.we usually choose a setting of 2 or 3 for our toasting.'),
(6506, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-11', 'Five Stars Thanks it replaced a 50 year old roster.'),
(6507, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-24', 'Five Stars This coffee maker is so good.'),
(6508, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-21', 'Great little blender This blender is amazing we absolutely love it. I make protein shakes weekly with some protein powder, yogurt, banana, ice, and water it works awesome. It blends it perfectly no chunks no powder. It is a super strong blender, I have filled it up to the rim before and been able to blend it and the shake comes out smooth. Sometimes you have to take it out and shake it up then re-blend other wise the blades get stuck and this horrible smell like it is jammed starts happening. When that happens I just lift it out shake, replace, and it keeps on blending. I have used to to blend other things as well like onions, jalapenos, fruit, etc it it a really nice powerful little blender.'),
(6509, 8, 1, 4, '2016-03-08', 'but makes a good cup of coffee without taking up a lot of ... Nothing fancy, but makes a good cup of coffee without taking up a lot of counter space. The carafe does drip and spill easily if poured too quickly.'),
(6510, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-12', 'Very nice coffeemaker Works like a charm!  So easy to fill with water (just remove the basin from the back, fill it up, and pop it back into place) and add coffee through the front \"door\" that pops open at the push of a button. Makes quality coffee (assuming you are also using quality coffee beans) as expected.  The adjustable warming options and brew strength are very nice and work well.  Programming it is also quite easy and works as expected. The slim design looks nice and isn\'t too much bigger than the small Kurig we used to have on the counter.'),
(6511, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Five Stars one year of use and still working!'),
(6512, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-02', 'Great purchase Excellent toaster with useful settings, easy to use.'),
(6513, 6, 1, 3, '2016-09-20', 'meh... wife says it toasts slower than ... meh...wife says it toasts slower than our old black and decker....but heck, it makes toast, and that\'s what I bought it for!.'),
(6514, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Performs as described This machine provide a quick cup of coffee on demand. It\'s computer recognition system \'tells\' you to add water as needed to the resovoir, or to choose which size cup of beverage that you are going to use. I have  not used it long enough to have the filter change alert to activate. Color wise, the  raspberry color is really not a true red as I had hoped. Overall, I am pleased with this machine. Actually, I am drinking less coffee instead of finishing off a pot out of guilt. The K- cups, I let them dry out on the sink and at the end of the day pry off the tops, clean out the grounds and filter inside and recycle the plastic.'),
(6515, 5, 1, 1, '2015-06-26', 'The coffee pot that does not work! We bought one. After a month it did not work at all. We returned it for another one. Same coffee pot. After 3 weeks it did not work at all. We returned it again. We appreciate the Amazon return policy, but I give this the lowest possible rating based on our experience!'),
(6516, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-29', 'Love this, so very glad that I purchased it Love this, so very glad that I purchased it. Love the way it toasts, just have to find the right setting.'),
(6517, 2, 1, 1, '2015-05-09', 'I am young with good eyes and it takes a magnifying glass to see ... DO NOT BUY THIS ITEM....it is a fire hazard, gets extremely hot on the outside as well as the cord and so hot on the inside you can\'t possibly expect to make toast in the thing.  It is also impossible to see the verbiage on the dials....I am young with good eyes and it takes a magnifying glass to see the verbiage.  Horrible product!'),
(6518, 11, 1, 5, '2015-03-09', 'Five Stars Very nice inexpensive functional toaster oven.'),
(6519, 7, 3, 4, '2015-05-19', 'Compact and user friendly, this coffee maker is much more flexible than my Keurig 2.0. It uses K-cup pods or my favorite ground coffee. There are three cups that fit in the brew head, an over all cup that holds the brew basket and the K-cup basket. Lift out the K-cup basket to use grounds, which has a MAX mark for convenience. The water reservoir has a lift out basket with 8, 10, and 14 oz marks for water. How much you put in is how much you get out, it doesnt hold extra water. The cup rest can be moved up one notch to fit smaller cups. The power button offers \"strong\" brew and regular brew. When all is set up and the power button is pushed, it takes about 45 seconds to know it is doing anything, then is starts to make slight \'boiling\' sounds then a murring sound as the coffee starts filling the cup. The whole brewing process takes less than three minutes. My favorite part of the coffee maker is that I can use grounds, which are less expensive. Yet I still have the fancy of using a K-cup pod if I wish. I have it set up in my home office, which is uber convenient. If I had found this maker first, it is the one I would have bought over the Keurig.'),
(6520, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-01', 'Four Stars easy set up ! easy clean up works for liquids only !'),
(6521, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-20', 'Five Stars Great.'),
(6522, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-14', 'Works great! Bought this to replace a 13 year old Cuisinart.  Wanted something smaller and was excited to find the toasting feature as well.  So far, no complaints!  Toasts well with the top slot and have used the bottom mainly for heating up pizza and small items.'),
(6523, 6, 1, 3, '2015-06-15', 'The best thing I can say about this toaster is that ... The best thing I can say about this toaster is that it looks good on the counter, and was relatively cheap. It does not toast consistently, and one side toasts noticeably darker than the other, in both slots. I have not used the \"programmed\" setting buttons on the side. If you\'re picky about how your toast is done, you may not be satisfied. The next toaster we buy will probably not be a Cuisinart.'),
(6524, 6, 1, 3, '2016-08-04', 'Three Stars Doesn\'t toast as dark as expected without putting the toast down twice.'),
(6525, 2, 1, 2, '2016-06-01', 'Two Stars bad temperature control, burns most things. bad timer.'),
(6526, 5, 1, 4, '2015-12-29', 'Four Stars Works well - love that I don\'t have to move it to fill the water container.'),
(6527, 8, 1, 1, '2014-07-09', 'check carefully. It broke right away.  It was inexpensive, but it would have saved me more money if I had not bought it.  And the descriptive was incorrect.'),
(6528, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Happy with purchase Happy with the function of this device after 3 weeks. No problems. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this unbiased review'),
(6529, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-11', 'Four Stars works good for blending protein shakes at work with ice and fruit.'),
(6530, 6, 1, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Five Stars Works great  good price too.'),
(6531, 10, 1, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Five Stars I just love it. Blends well very quickly, does everything I wanted. Easy to clean too!'),
(6532, 4, 1, 4, '2015-04-29', 'Works good, looks good, doesn\'t cost an arm and a leg I like this nice, reasonably priced toaster oven. It\'s attractive, the controls are simple, it\'s roomy without being enormous. The toast setting is kind of tricky, though --  \"medium\" gives me burnt toast. A hair above the \"light\" setting gives me what I consider medium. Also, I\'m intrigued by the \"bagel\" setting. As far as I can tell, it\'s identical to the \"toast\" setting.'),
(6533, 10, 1, 5, '2016-07-14', 'Five Stars Durable convenient and easy. Still working after 4 years.'),
(6534, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-11', 'I was sad. _ Motor died after 3 smoothies. I was sad. _'),
(6535, 10, 1, 3, '2015-12-02', 'Decent for price BLENDS GREAT. HARD TO CLEAN'),
(6536, 6, 1, 2, '2015-07-14', 'I hate to be stuck with a defective toaster The right hand slot only toast on one side. The toaster was delivered June 1st. On July 14th I decided to exchange it for one that is not defective. My response was that it was not eligeable for return. I hate to be stuck with a defective toaster.'),
(6537, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-03', 'Great product for the price! I\'ve been using it for a month now, and it works perfectly fine! However, I never press and hold the power button, I rather pulse it since I am aware that the motor is not too powerful. But even when pulsing, this blender makes perfect smoothies and shakes. I would totally recommend -- great product for the price!'),
(6538, 4, 1, 1, '2015-05-03', 'What a rip off! Had a Black & Decker for probably 20 years of family use and it was developing some problem that I can\'t even remember now, but after all those years, I had no regrets buying a new toaster oven.  Now, like so many others, the bottom coils are now way warped, probably an inch higher in the center.  (In less than 2 years of use)  From what others say, at this point, the rod will split and a good chance of a fire.  The day I will spend $38.00+ to ship it back, only as other have mentioned the replacement coils go bad later, will be the day in hell.  How can a former name like Cuisinart screw people like this?  There is no shame in producing such crap these days.  Hope the whole company goes under some day.  You have been warned about this product.'),
(6539, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-13', 'A delightful machine We have used this coffee maker for three months now, and I must say it has been a delight.  We previously were using the Bunn velocity brewer but grew weary of of the many issues we had with the premium priced machine.  This little brewer does a superb job at brewing tasty coffee in a streamlined and smart design.  The thought of this machine, from the gliders on the bottom, to the removable tank all add to the ease of the daily ritual of brewing coffee. The carafe works as advertised.  We did not find the fact it takes longer than the Bunn\'s three minute brewing as a large set back.  Indeed, the anticipation of a good cup (or sneaking an initial cup with the stop and pour feature) add to the experience.  A worthwhile purchase!'),
(6540, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-13', 'Five Stars Really a sturdy, great blender for the price.  I use this one at my office.'),
(6541, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Five Stars Easy to use. Takes up less room than expected. Loved the color. I found this machine to be quieter than older models. Thanks keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(6542, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-29', 'We love how quickly it makes the coffee I got this as a house warming gift and have been loving it. We love how quickly it makes the coffee, that everybody can have a different type/flavor of coffee and we aren\'t finding it too hard to find deals on the cups  - which was the thing always holding us back. We also like the option of using the carafe though we haven\'t bought one yet. The only reason I didn\'t give it 5 stars is simply because I find the new technology that doesn\'t allow non-keurig cups frustrating. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(6543, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-18', 'Five Stars Love my new coffee pot'),
(6544, 9, 1, 2, '2016-01-04', 'Very Disappointed I was so excited to find this coffee maker. I had been looking for a carafe - free coffee maker for months. It is beautiful aesthetically. It worked great for two uses. Then the coffee would no longer come out hot. It was barely luke warm. I am reordering it in hopes that this was just a defective model. Stay tuned.'),
(6545, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-26', 'Good buy So far, very happy with purchase.  Well priced and offers just enough features.'),
(6546, 5, 1, 3, '2016-10-26', 'It makes coffee just fine, nothing fancy We have had this maybe 2 weeks. The front plate fell off right away. I didn\'t bother with it because I have no back up coffee maker! We will buy a different coffee maker and return this one. It makes coffee just fine, nothing fancy, but I expect better quality for such a basic machine that will be needed every single day!.'),
(6547, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-18', 'Great for single dispensing coffee Our old one broke after eight years, so naturally we bought another one. Great for single dispensing coffee, keeps it hot'),
(6548, 3, 1, 4, '2015-01-11', 'So far it seems to be doing well. Since ... So far it seems to be doing well. Since it is has buttons rather than dials, I\'m hoping they don\'t give out. I\'ve always had toaster ovens and I\'m enjoying the convection option. I haven\'t had full use of it yet, but the Black & Deckers have served me well in the past.'),
(6549, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-21', 'Great! Just the right size and blends very well.'),
(6550, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-09', 'Before this toaster, I would have to wait 20 ... Before this toaster, I would have to wait 20 minutes for my oven to heat up. Now I can instantly have toast, english muffins, and tater tots!'),
(6551, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-30', 'Fabulous Tiny Blender!! This is a fabulous blender. I could not be more happy. I make a smoothy every morning for breakfast and was dragging out my commercial blender, It was such a pain. This tiny blender can sit out as it is so small. The jar serves as a cup and has a cap that can go with you. I has a great motor that does exactly what I needed it for. I could not be happier!'),
(6552, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-24', 'Five Stars Good Job!'),
(6553, 4, 1, 2, '2015-07-08', 'Another Burner Oven I\'m giving up on toaster ovens - third mediocre one in a row.  Bought this to replace another unit with essentially 2 toast settings.  It had a digital control with a scale of 1 - 10.  Anything over 3 was black.  This unit has an analog controls for finer settings.  So far so good, but I have to keep the control between the 9:00 and 9:30 position.  The 10:00 position will significantly blacken bread and just about light frosted pop tarts on fire.  The limited useful range of the toast control makes it difficult to adjust consistently for different foods. The multi-position rack is also poorly designed for the most common usage of toasting.  Installing it in the toast position (so the rack pull-out lever works and the bread is at the mid-point of the elements) puts the front cross bar of the rack above the wires that support the food.  That makes it impossible to slide the toast out.  It has to be lifted over the front bar.  Flipping the rack over puts the bottom closer to the elements than the top.  That\'s good for doing bagels cut side down, but not so good for bread. Now begins the search for a decent toaster. Update: - I just noticed that the rack on mine does not match the picture.  The small support wires are welded on the opposite side of the larger frame wires which creates the issue with toast not sliding out easily.'),
(6554, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-15', 'Five Stars Better than i had wished for.'),
(6555, 3, 1, 3, '2015-12-22', 'Decent for the price, but some stupid design flaws... I\'ll keep this short, and maybe revise later.  After limited use so far, it seems to be working fine, but there are three aspects of this oven that prevent me from giving it more than 3 stars: 1.  The writing rubs off easily.  In fact, part of the lettering was already off when we received it.  I had this issue with our previous oven (a Cuisinart), so it\'s common enough.  It may very well get to the point after a year of regular cleaning, that there will be no lettering left. 2.  The door has nothing stopping it from slamming into your countertop.  If you\'re a little clumsy, this means you could scratch your countertop or possibly even damage the door if it slips out of your hand.  Most importantly, the handle rests directly on the counter, and in order to close it, you have to slide your hand under it.  If you miss, you might slide your hand between the handle and the glass, which gets very hot, and burn yourself.  This could have easily been avoided by including a catch that prevents the door from opening past horizontal, or simply reshaping the handle so that the corners come into contact with the counter (perhaps with some rubber bumpers on there) and leaving a gap under the middle of the handle. 3.  It makes totally unnecessary and obnoxious beeps every time you press buttons.  Some feedback is warranted, because the buttons themselves are mushy, but the volume is unnecessarily loud when you\'re standing right next to it.'),
(6556, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-14', 'A MUST Have in every household! We love our Keurig Brewing System!  The best coffee make we ever owned!.'),
(6557, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-07', 'Great little countertop oven appliance! I believe I made a great choice of this toaster oven, after reading many reviews of this product.  I needed a small oven for small amounts of items that I frequently need to bake...I hate to turn on my big oven for these small tasks.  So far,  this unit fits the bill.  I haven\'t tried toasting in it as I have a reliable toaster but am sure it will be as adequate as the oven feature is.  So far, I love this B&D toaster oven...and the price was very reasonable!.'),
(6558, 3, 1, 1, '2015-12-30', 'No rack, unit is useless. Nice unit to look at but it the package did not include the rack, therefore it is useless at this point.'),
(6559, 9, 1, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Five Stars Absolutely love this'),
(6560, 7, 3, 5, '2014-01-25', 'My review with the item is great! With the delivery (pick up at store) was not good. Shipping was delayed to me but stores had a bunch of them. I originally ordered item online because the stores in my area (Millersburg, Ashland and Wooster) did not have any of this item (out of stock). I feel I should have gotten my order the same time they items came into the store.'),
(6561, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-24', 'One Star After only 3 uses it no longer works.'),
(6562, 5, 1, 3, '2015-06-23', 'Good coffee but short lived We have had this coffee maker for 2 years and it just died.  We thought the coffee it made was great.  Consistent, great taste, just the right temperature.  It was very easy to use with perfect simple programming options.  But it started to leak some water a few months ago and then one day it just didn\'t turn on.  I would expect a coffee maker to last more than two years, especially one as straight forward as this one.'),
(6563, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Great value. Has so many uses Great value.  Has so many uses.  Love this'),
(6564, 5, 1, 4, '2015-06-18', 'Best Coffee Maker I\'ve Owned We demoted our 4-year old Keurig and went back to having a \"real\" coffee maker.  Saw that this one was highly rated by customers on Amazon and it does NOT disappoint!  Easily the most intuitive coffee maker I have owned.  I love the removable water tank, which makes getting ready for a fresh batch of coffee so easy. Pros: -Removable water tank.  Just lift up and take it over to the sink to fill.  Still gives you the option to fill the water with the carafe the old-school way. -Adjustable brew strength -Adjustable \"keep warm\" temperature -Easy to set up the Auto Program feature -2-hour auto-shutoff - Carafe pours without dripping Cons: -Can be tough to see how much coffee is in the carafe just by glancing at it. -Fit and finish is not perfect.  When I close the coffee grind compartment, it appears a little slanted.  Nothing seems to be broken, though. -Tough to get every last drop out of the carafe without holding it completely upside down.'),
(6565, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-31', 'Five Stars I love this thing'),
(6566, 11, 1, 5, '2015-02-20', 'Picture perfect Reliable and Sturdy. Delivery was on point.'),
(6567, 11, 1, 3, '2014-09-24', 'Possibly too small. I really like how small&compact this toaster oven is. However, because it is so small if food touches the top heater it will start on fire. So please be careful!!!'),
(6568, 7, 3, 5, '2014-10-10', 'Love it, easy to use, and clean. It is fast too'),
(6569, 6, 1, 2, '2015-07-03', 'I was not pleased with my purchase I was not pleased with my purchase.  Does not toast evenly.  Toaster slots are too small for larger bread.  Did not fit my needs at all.'),
(6570, 9, 1, 5, '2015-07-08', 'I am in love I love this coffee pot. I would not buy another coffee pot unless they quit making these and that would kill me. This is the second pot  that I have had  .My son broke some thing on the other pot while I was away. I can fix my pot at night, it will be ready when I wake up and my coffee is just rite.I can make up to twelve cups or as little as 4 cups. The coffee does not get stale or rancid by staying in the chamber since it iis timed as to when the heat will stop.. I do love this pot and I would highly recomend it to anyone in the market for a new coffee pot.'),
(6571, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Five Stars Great quality product'),
(6572, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'Five Stars Works wonderfully.'),
(6573, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-14', 'One Star cant even blend an apple...!!!'),
(6574, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-05', 'Five Stars was as expected. Great'),
(6575, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-08', 'Great Buy Very nice coffee maker.  Easy to fill with water.  Turns around easily for access to the water container.  Clock is easy to see, several brew settings that work great.'),
(6576, 8, 1, 4, '2016-02-10', 'Four Stars It\'s ok. I don\'t know why it keeps making that percolating noise when it\'s clearly done.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(6577, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-22', 'Easy to clean Works okay. Doesn\'t make the coffee taste weird. Easy to clean. Doesn\'t take up too much counter space'),
(6578, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', '5 Stars I don\'t know how I ever made food before this toaster oven. Heats perfect with lots of toasting adjustment, bakes everything and preheats in just a minute or two and uses a lot less energy than an oven. The convection bakes things in about 5-10 minutes vs 30-45 minutes in a standard oven!! This is replacing my microwave for most everything except maybe microwave popcorn, which I could live without anyway. I make plenty of food from frozen and it does beautifully cooking food through and crisping things without burning if your careful whereas the microwave made food chewy and hard. The digital buttons are so easy to use but reading the quick start manual/guide is essential to know which buttons to push first in order to set the timer, toast adjustment, and temperature controls. Buttons are really easy even for a non-tech savvy person. It is smaller than some dimensions online quote, and even the box it came in had wrong dimensions. It fits on a small space on the countertop but you can put full sized plates to bake and pizzas in it. I\'m glad I didn\'t buy a \"compact\" size oven, not sure it would fit much for food in it or be worth taking up any counter space.'),
(6579, 3, 1, 4, '2015-05-10', 'Although I like this toaster oven the controls can get a little ... Although I like this toaster oven the controls can get a little use to. No big deal and im probably just use to my old one. Other than I have no complaints.'),
(6580, 10, 1, 4, '2015-12-12', 'Quite handy though small It is small - but quite handy... We have used it couple of times and liked the product'),
(6581, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-10', 'Five Stars Good if you live alone and is single.'),
(6582, 10, 1, 1, '2015-02-02', 'so i held the lid with my hands when using it but still works terribly. i dont recommend people to buy it at ... this is a junk. i bought it in fall but didn\'t have a chance to use it until now. I put fruits inside and this lid is not working. my pieces of fruits were everywhere. so i held the lid with my hands when using it but still works terribly. i dont recommend people to buy it at all. looks cute but doesn\'t work at all.'),
(6583, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-21', 'Five Stars K'),
(6584, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-19', 'Great for the price Great toaster oven. We are getting used to the \"knob\" on and off. A switch would be easier.'),
(6585, 2, 1, 3, '2016-03-08', 'Otherwise it\'s good. Melted plastic smell every time I use it. Otherwise it\'s good.'),
(6586, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-09', 'have made toast in it several times and it is just like I like it,  good and crunchy. have also heated things in it and it work. Love it.'),
(6587, 4, 1, 1, '2015-12-07', 'Disappointed with Cuisinart TOB-40 After 3 years and 2 months (2 months past the warranty), it has problems shutting off.  Burner elements stay on even when turning the switch to \"off\".  Had to unplug it to get it to shut off.  This has happened to us twice now.  No matter what temp the oven is set to, the elements stay on the entire time.  Cuisinart doesn\'t sell repair parts.  Mine will soon be taking up space in the landfill.  I was expecting a few more years from a Cuisinart product.'),
(6588, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-26', 'Great value makes great smoothies I use to make my smoothies and it works great for that.'),
(6589, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-06', 'A fine toaster oven Works great. Have had no problems. The rack holding the tray is unique and I can see that be l being usual. Several cooking options available.'),
(6590, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-10', 'Five Stars i love my keurig'),
(6591, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-05', 'Made great gifts I bought two for gifts. My friends really like them!'),
(6592, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-21', 'A perfect cup of coffee! I have owned a couple Keurig coffee machines, but this one is my favorite! I don\'t need to wait for the water to heat up like some of the older models I just select my size and it\'s ready to go. You can only use Keurig approved k-cups unless you purchase a freedom clip or rig it up to disconnect the sensor. I wouldn\'t suggest that, because these machines cost too much to destroy by cutting wires. If you use your own k-cup filters the pink filters work with any issues. I love getting a perfect cup of coffee every time!.'),
(6593, 6, 1, 2, '2015-05-23', 'greatly disappointed in amazon.com we purchased this toaster from amazon.com primarily, no singularly, because it was advertised \'made in America\'.  it is not!  It is made in China'),
(6594, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-08', 'Brews better than the old coffee maker we had We\'ve had this for a few months now.  Brews better than the old coffee maker we had,  easier to clean, program, the bold brewing selector is a nice feature, & all around very pleased.'),
(6595, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'it works just fine. Its perfect for making smothie and fresh juice So far, it works just fine. Its perfect for making smothie and fresh juice. Yum!'),
(6596, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-01', 'good toaster - would buy again Good toaster. I haven\'t noticed any of the uneven toasting that others commented about.  I like how the handle will bring up the toast just a little bit more after it pops up, since I toast a lot of english muffins that are short.  The white plastic out casing is a nice complement to my kitchen.  I would buy it again.  It was packaged well and arrived safely'),
(6597, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Makes a great cup of coffee This has worked really well for me so far. Makes a great cup of coffee, and I love the option to make a \"strong\" cup. There are only a few things I would change if I could. First of all, I know a few of the higher models come with the carafe included, and I wish this one did too. In addition, I wish they would go back to the metal covering on the drip tray, the plastic makes it feel like a cheaper piece. Finally, I wish you could increase the hot water setting to more than 6oz. The coffee goes up to 10oz, so not sure why you shouldnt be able to do this with water as well. But overall, a great product, and I\'m very happy with my purchase. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(6598, 6, 1, 1, '2016-07-29', 'DON\"T BUY THIS TOASTER!! This is a cheap piece of crap for the price!!  I wish to God I had my 1960\'s Sunbeam Toaster.  It did not burn the toast on one side, and the quality was SO much better.'),
(6599, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-11', 'CLEAN AND SIMPLE!  PERFECT! Studied hard looking for best coffee maker.  I focused on clean, simple and hoped for decent coffee.  I am THRILLED with this product.  For only $37, I bought the CLEANEST and MOST SIMPLE coffee maker.  I can pull out the water tank and fill.  This allows no dripping and easy cleaning if I ever clean it.  My last fancy coffee maker, I tried to clean the internal water tank twice.  First time I spill water on the grinder motor and broke it.  The next time I got paper towels wedged in a crevice that I barely got out.  Never could clean it well.  My old coffee maker also had a cover over the coffee filter.  This cover had lots of grooves and was impossible to clean.  My old maker had a stainless carafe.  I worried I may need one, but I\'m thrilled with the glass and heater that keeps coffee very hot.  I also like to be able to see inside how much coffee I have.  Small negatives that I\'ll happlily overlook because of the low price are: bit flimsy and blue light.  Could a $10-30 Mr Coffee be better?  Hamilton Beach is hard to beat.'),
(6600, 8, 1, 4, '2015-12-02', 'Like I wanted a smaller coffee maker and its what I wanted.'),
(6601, 8, 1, 2, '2016-10-13', 'Good for the price but I would recommend buying something ... Missing the part that stops the coffee from pouring when the pot is lifted. Good for the price but I would recommend buying something more expensive.'),
(6602, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-01', 'Sucks Bought this to replace an older Black & Decker toaster. This toaster is nearly impossible to set the same each time. It doesn\'t get very hot and takes a long time to toast bread. The setting is so difficult that you never know if toast will not be done enough or burned. I have had it too long to return so I will probably have to just buy something else to replace it with. Would not recommend this toaster.'),
(6603, 8, 1, 4, '2016-07-09', 'Great little pot for the Money! Great little coffee maker. And good value. Drip-free pouring, and makes good coffee. If it would turn itself off when I forget, I\'d give it 5 stars in a heartbeat.'),
(6604, 6, 1, 4, '2016-10-08', 'This is a nice looking toaster which does its job This is a nice looking toaster which does its job. However sometimes it burns corners of my toasts. Couple of times it started my fire alarm:).'),
(6605, 8, 1, 4, '2016-04-22', 'Makes good coffee but he can\'t move the coffee pot Great size just enough coffee makes good coffee.  Unlike larger pots this one keeps running when you remove the pot.'),
(6606, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-17', 'Great buy Love it! Not a single problem, cooks perfect.'),
(6607, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-13', 'Easy to use toaster oven I like that I can toast, bake and reheat anything. Easy to use and doesn\'t take up a lo of space on my counter. very satisfied!'),
(6608, 12, 1, 5, '2015-08-15', 'Five Stars I love this toaster, I didn\'t want a monster and this is just right and good looking!'),
(6609, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Five Stars Works well.'),
(6610, 11, 1, 1, '2014-06-24', 'Toaster Oven Smoking I bought this Black & Decker toaster oven to replace one I had before.  This one started to smoke.  I thought that might be from crumbs, cleaned them off, and the next time I used the toaster it still smoked.  I\'m returning it.'),
(6611, 7, 3, 3, '2016-12-17', 'does not hold enough water for a cup'),
(6612, 2, 1, 1, '2016-03-09', 'This toaster is much smaller than it looks. It ... This toaster is much smaller than it looks. It will not heat a thick slice of pizza due to its size.'),
(6613, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-03', 'Five Stars Purchased for my elderly sister - she absolutely LUVs this model of the Hamilton Beach Toast Station'),
(6614, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-28', 'great design perfect.'),
(6615, 5, 1, 2, '2015-05-18', 'Great machine for a great price Had to get a new coffeemaker since our calphalon one bit the dust.  Searched high and low, read all reviews, and ended up with this one.  We were sick of paying high dollar for a machine that literally dies in a couple of years or is on a crazy recall list for potential fire hazards!  Settled on this one and haven\'t been disappointed.  Works well, makes a decent pot of coffee, and I like the ease of use with the timer and clock.  As others have noted, this one does NOT have a bell or signal to let you know when it\'s done brewing, and I kind of don\'t like that.  But it\'s so minor I can live without it.  I love that you can remove the tank and fill it directly with water at your fridge or sink, etc., instead of filling the pot up and then pouring into the tank.  Just one less step and it\'s a nice touch.  Have had it about 3 months now and not a single hiccup! UPDATED REVIEW 9/9/2015 - The machine has been working fine.  However, I accidentally shattered the carafe and have found literally IMPOSSIBLE to locate a replacement after days of online searching.  I just got off the phone with Hamilton Beach directly begging them to please put me on some sort of list so that when or IF they ever come back in stock, I can immediately order.  The best they can tell me is it will be back in stock \"in 2-4 weeks best case scenario, but most likely later\", and they will NOT put me on a list.  Totally unacceptable.  So yeah, I\'m trashing this thing and having to purchase yet another coffee maker.  I simply can\'t wait over 4 weeks to get a simple carafe replacement!  Totally NOT WORTH THE MONEY to have this for less than 7 months and not be able to purchase the most likely needed replacement part.'),
(6616, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-07', 'Perfect. This is my second one. Other lasted quite awhile, but toaster part stopped working. I had it for six years with lots of use. Make sure you are buying the black model #22708. That is the good quality one.'),
(6617, 6, 1, 4, '2016-03-14', 'Better than average. Very good toaster in that it toasts quickly and evenly. Do wish it had a crumb tray.'),
(6618, 1, 1, 5, '2016-07-19', 'Housewarming Bought it for my son and daughter in-law. They fell in love with mine and are enjoying it.'),
(6619, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-26', 'Love the Oven. Live the Oven. I could probably cook everything in this lovely, easy-to-use, totally dependable toaster oven. Virtually negates the need for an actual oven and stove.'),
(6620, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', '... a gift and my son & his wife really like it and have done nothing but rave about it this was a gift and my son & his wife really like it and have done nothing but rave about it.'),
(6621, 7, 3, 1, '2016-08-20', 'i bought a flexbrew approximately 6 months ago. 3 months ago it stopped working - would not pull water from the tank, even after regular cleaning. would brew and brew and nothing in the cup. contacted hamilton beach and they were great - sent me a replacement machine. i have had that machine for 2 months now, and same issue -will not pull water from the reservoir to brew. i will not purchase again and would not recommend this product.'),
(6622, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'What a nice upgrade from the original! Love this new and updated machine! WOW! what a upgrade from the original Keurig machine. Not only does this machine feature 4 different oz\'s but it provides a really nice touch screen  feature that the original was lacking. The machine is very compact and brews a nice cup of coffee every time with the touch of a few easy buttons. Like other reviews, I did think the carafe was included. I was so intrigued that I went out the next day to buy the thermal carafe so I could see it in action. Such a nice feature to have! I love to use this pot when I have company over instead of brewing a single cup. One con is that I wish the coffee brewed hotter. Overall,  If your a fan of keurig I recommend this machine! I received this product free for testing purposes but opinions are my own.'),
(6623, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-06', 'Five Stars its a keurig.'),
(6624, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-07', 'I just love this so far I just love this so far. I have always hated the uneven toasting function of toaster ovens. But occasionally wish I had one. Replaces two appliances if you don\'t have lots of space for them.'),
(6625, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-19', 'One of the best there is! I love fresh coffee in the morning, a grinder for the beans, and it\'s the best coffee you can get!!!'),
(6626, 6, 1, 4, '2014-09-13', 'Don\'t use the higher settings or everything will be burnt ... Don\'t use the higher settings or everything will be burnt. When making a bagel I actually had to turn the knob down and not use the bagel setting or my bagels were too hard.'),
(6627, 7, 3, 1, '2014-07-14', 'I didn\'t like this and maybe the one I got was defective. But it made aweful noises and when it was brewing so much steam came out it looked like smoke rolling and I was afraid it was going to catch on fire. I took mine back and got a Keurig.'),
(6628, 9, 1, 4, '2016-06-13', 'Great alternative to the Keurig! Love this coffee maker. Set it on timer and it\'s ready in the morning. Pop my cup underneath To dispense hot coffee when I\'m ready. You do need to occasional clean the valve. If it gets coffee grounds in it, it will leak. Learned this the hard way. Woke up to a counter and floor full of coffee'),
(6629, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-07', 'Awesome: ) little smaller then expected but fits in ... Awesome:) little smaller then expected but fits in my kitchen perfect.'),
(6630, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-31', 'poor performance I have been using this toaster for over a month, and I am very disappointed.  It does not toast evenly.  Before I made this purchase I was using a Sunbeam toaster I had for about 10 years and it still worked good, (costing only $10.00). If you like your toast evenly toasted, buy something else.'),
(6631, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'Recommended Recommended'),
(6632, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-24', 'a coffee brewer that has a removable water reservoir that can be easily washed. Also like the little wheels on the ... Finally, a coffee brewer that has a removable water reservoir that can be easily washed.  Also like the little wheels on the bottom which make it easy to move the unit around.  Hooray !'),
(6633, 4, 1, 1, '2015-04-12', 'Dangerous Dangerous overheating, the back of the case melted to power cord. Was not in contact directly with the case.'),
(6634, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-18', 'Great coffee maker, great price So, my main goal in purchasing a new coffee maker was getting one that didn\'t dribble.  This is that coffee maker.  As a perk, I also got one that I can leave on for more than 30 minutes without the coffee tasting burnt because of the adjustable temperature for the heat plate.  Its easy to fill the water container and can be set to a stronger brew which takes a little longer but its worth the wait to me.  As for all the hub bub on how good the coffee tastes...it tastes good to me but I don\'t claim to be a coffee expert.  We are very happy with this brewer and the coffee that it makes.'),
(6635, 2, 1, 4, '2015-09-28', 'Well built and nice in appearance Well built and nice in appearance. No height adjustment for the tray which is a downside. The timing knob also isn\'t scaled very well, there is a very fine line between nicely toasted and burnt. Good toaster for the price.'),
(6636, 2, 1, 3, '2016-07-01', '... this had so when I brought it I was like a kid in a candy store once I got ... I was very excited reading all the reviews this had so when I brought it I was like a kid in a candy store once I got it out of the box it had a scratch on top still ok with it bust not a 5 star rating so I give it a 3'),
(6637, 8, 1, 1, '2016-05-16', 'Incredibly noisy! I\'m kind of a coffee snob so ... Incredibly noisy!  I\'m kind of a coffee snob so always purchase \"good \" coffee and grind my beans right before making.  I\'ve had this cup for about a month and every pot tastes harsh and nasty-----like the office jumbo pot at the end of the day!!!'),
(6638, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-12', 'Five Stars Love it. Toasts even and works great'),
(6639, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-13', 'Great coffee... This is a great coffee maker. The 1-4 cup setting actually does make a difference.'),
(6640, 11, 1, 4, '2014-01-03', 'Very good buy! Works great! Does what it supposed to do. Makes toast and heats up pizzas. Plus other snacks. Really good size for my counter top.'),
(6641, 11, 1, 5, '2015-07-26', 'No problems yet Was looking for a good cheap toaster and this was the one.'),
(6642, 1, 1, 5, '2016-04-23', 'Great Brewer Love this brewer.  Smaller than the big one I had before.  Takes small space on counter.  I wish the color was brighter.  I haven\'t use the carafe part, don\'t really need that.  Don\'t hesitate to buy one of these in your favorite color.'),
(6643, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'Five Stars Nice packaged'),
(6644, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-16', 'I like it. The size is perfect for small counters I like it. The size is perfect for small counters. The heating elements get glowing hot quickly.  I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 because of the loud timer ticking.'),
(6645, 5, 1, 5, '2014-02-17', 'Perfect design and great coffee I like how the water reservoir detaches and everything is easy to clean.  Really glad I got this and the price was cheaper than most other coffeemakers.'),
(6646, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-23', 'Hamilton Beach 46201 This is an excellent coffee maker. It reflects a well thought out design. Adding water and coffee is very convenient and easy. It does not leak or splash. Paper filters do not stick to the basket. The programmable features are very easy and quick to set and if there is a power glitch in the middle of the night, you will not wake up in the morning to a cold pot of coffee. Kudos to the Hamilton Beach engineers for actually designing (and possibly even testing?) a functional product. This is an excellent coffee maker!'),
(6647, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-05', 'Great One-Person Blender This is a great little blender. I\'ve used it about once a week for a couple months and haven\'t had any problems. For ~$15, the is a perfect blender for one-person use. PROS: -Very powerful motor that will blend anything you want -Great for smaller blending needs (single person making shake or smoothie) -Extremely easy to operate CONS: -Cleaning around the blades in the bottom of the \'cup\' is a bit of a pain -Sometimes the lid is a little difficult to get on -Sometimes has a bit of a mechanical/motor smell, but it isn\'t too prevalent'),
(6648, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-04', 'It arrived in an outstanding condition and I just hope that the oven is as good as the reviews A replacement for my previous oven of 6 years. It arrived in an outstanding condition and I just hope that the oven is as good as the reviews.'),
(6649, 11, 1, 3, '2015-07-07', 'Three Stars I preferred my older version to the new one.'),
(6650, 7, 3, 5, '2015-06-22', 'I just purchased this machine for my RV and find it much better than my Keurig - and I have had three different Keurigs. The coffee is always really hot and you can use your own coffee as well as K cups.'),
(6651, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-26', 'Love it love it love it Love it love it love it!!! It explains step by step how to clean the machine thoroughly with vinegar. No other brand explains that well about how to clean. My mr.coffee stopped working after a year even with my regular cleaning. Since i just did what they explained to do, clean button on the machine!! However, this vinegar cleaning is so far sooooo good, since i get good tasted coffee every morning with every month\'s vinegar cleaning. Also, love the fact that the water reservoir actually is detached from the machine. It is very convenient and practically good machine. Already recommened to many of my friends'),
(6652, 8, 1, 5, '2016-05-12', 'Nice little coffee maker that does what it\'s supposed to ... Nice little coffee maker that does what it\'s supposed to do,and fits right in with my other counter top items. Since I\'m not a 4-5 cup a day coffee drinker,this does the trick! It\'s worth the money that\'s not expensive at all. BUY THIS!'),
(6653, 7, 3, 4, '2015-10-16', 'For a single cup it is ok. I have used only twice since I just received it. I used a Kcup and it was fine.'),
(6654, 4, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'Five Stars great oven'),
(6655, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-20', 'Great coffee maker. What a good coffee pot.  I have used Cuisinart\'s for years, but with the recent change in quality and home fire with those pots, I decided to try this, I have to say makes very good coffee, its only draw back is not being able to set the time duration for the burner to stay on after making a pot.  But it is not a deal breaker at all, and it does have 3 temp setting for keeping the coffee warm, the low setting seems to do well for not burning the coffee. The pull out water container saves a step, not having to fill the pot then pour into water area, really makes the process much faster.  its not quite the chore it was. So far no safety issues.  I\'ll update periodically if anything happens. Note * I am a coffee hound, I like good coffee, brewing is so important, and this really does seem to make good coffee, given the style and price range.'),
(6656, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-08', 'Does the trick! I was skeptical because of the size, but all in all it does what I need it to do, and does it well. Glad I went for this one over the more expensive ones.'),
(6657, 4, 1, 4, '2016-06-20', 'Especially good for single seniors A must for the apartment. Especially good for single seniors. Easy to use and keep clean.'),
(6658, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Love it only one gripe!!! Love this Keurig model! It\'s sleeker more compact design fits perfectly on counter without taking up so much space! I love touch screen & karaf brewing option that older models didn\'t have. My only gripe like so many others;  is not all \"k-cups\" will register to work in brewer; I have hot chocolate k-cups from Keurig that the brewer says is not a k-cup it can use?!?! And yet it does register non Keurig coffee pods?!?! Thankfully the hot chocolate pods not working are an easy fix! Other than that I love this brewer & would recommend it!'),
(6659, 10, 1, 1, '2015-10-26', 'Weak Motor, don\'t waste your money Weak Motor! Bought it to use for shakeology shakes.  Used for just over 30 days to blend 8 oz of milk, shake mix, 1/2 a banana and 3 cubes of ice.  The motor slowed this morning and now wont blend.  We have a normal large blender and wanted the individual one for ease of clean up. I wouldn\'t recommend this, the reviews are misleading... it should work for more than 30 days.'),
(6660, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-18', 'Five Stars good'),
(6661, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-05', 'Great  coffee from this pot We ordered this when our old free from a coffee company, pot quit.  I checked out the reviews and chose this one. Well, we love it. my hubby uses the bold setting and says it makes great coffee. I am not a coffee drinker so I am giving this review on his word, and he really knows coffee.'),
(6662, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'It was love at first cup I am 57years old and have never been a very big coffee drinker until I bought my Keurig. I used to own an Black N Decker Space maker under the cabinet coffee maker and would brew a pot of coffee, have one cup and discover moldy grounds and an unfinished pot of coffee a week later. When I broke my coffee pot and went shopping for a new coffee maker I stumbled unto a new Keurig at Bed, Bath & Beyond. It was love at first cup! I now enjoy coffee a different way nearly everyday and now I brew a pot and put it in the fridge and enjoy ice coffee the next day. I can\'t imagine living without my Keurig and I reccommend it highly.'),
(6663, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-01', 'Five Stars It is working very well.  It is easier to pick the toast.'),
(6664, 2, 1, 3, '2015-01-23', 'Not a great toaster. But none of them are Not a great toaster. But none of them are. Even the $200+ ones. The GE I had 20 years ago was terrific. They don\'t make them like that anymore.'),
(6665, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-03', 'Five Stars great size for one--pretty quiet--works great'),
(6666, 3, 1, 1, '2015-03-05', 'did not explain how bad is did not  explain how bad is broken'),
(6667, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-19', 'One Star Broken after 6 weeks - spring mechanism snapped and timer failed. Oven is hazardous as it won\'t turn off.'),
(6668, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'I\'m in love! Let me start by telling you this is my second Keurig, I\'m a fan. My last one was the Vue which I loved but it was difficult to find Vue cups. Frustrated,  I decided to give up on all things Keurig. Then they came out with this beauty... Here is a list of reasons I fell in love with my 2.0. 1. The price is nice!  Anywhere from $90 to $130 depending on where you are shopping.  Not bad for a quality brewer. 2. The design.  It\'s not as bulky as some of the other brewers,  the touch screen is very user friendly,  and I like that the water reservoir is on the back of the brewer. 3. The selection of kcups! I was worried about this one.  All the research I read said that many kcups would not work in this brewer.  Well,  I\'m here to tell you that in my experience, that is not true!  So far I have not found one kcup that didn\'t work.  I\'ve used off brands (cups without the \"keurig stamp\" on them), and the eco refillable cup and they have all worked! 4. The speed on this thing!  It brews a 10oz cup in seconds and preheats in no time flat. 5. Taste!  Every single cup comes out steamy and delicious. I haven\'t had the chance to go grab the carafe so I can\'t give you a review on that but I plan on purchasing soon. I really don\'t have a single bad thing to say about this product. I\'d recommend it to friends,  buy it again,  and purchase it for family and friends.  5 stars all the way! *I received my brewer  complimentary for reviewing purposes*'),
(6669, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-01', 'This is the one to get We had a Cuisinart toaster that lasted a long time but were hesitant to buy a new one it because some reviews said it produced chemical odors. Finally, we decided it was the right one to replace the old toaster we had given away when we moved. We\'re just delighted with it. It has all the right features, produces no unpleasant or unusual odors. It makes toast perfectly each time. My wife and I highly recommend it!  We tried and returned three others for one reason or another and ended up loving this moderately priced one the most.'),
(6670, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'Five Stars Very happy, finally hot coffee !'),
(6671, 9, 1, 3, '2015-03-21', 'Three Stars Works fine for 4 months and then started leaking'),
(6672, 6, 1, 4, '2016-02-27', 'Good reviews on consumer reports Good reviews on consumer reports so we got it.  Glad we did.'),
(6673, 3, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Controls with options are easy to become accustomed to and they perform well Sleek design. Controls with options are easy to become accustomed to and they perform well. Very happy with the oven.'),
(6674, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-03', 'Five Stars This toaster works like it is supposed to. I would recommend this product to anyone.'),
(6675, 5, 1, 4, '2014-07-02', 'Mmm Good Coffee! I really like this coffee maker and recommend it. It does what it is advertised to do. Has a small countertop footprint and a snug decanter fit along with the other features. My only complaint, and the reason it gets only 4 stars, is that the four little \"wheels\" on the bottom don\'t really work as hoped. There are four wheels that are supposed to turn the unit around for easy access to the water tank in the rear. I placed the coffee maker on a smooth granite countertop and I still can\'t turn it around easily. It\'s the same as if they just don\'t exist so I was disappointed with that. However I did read the reviews and some people like this feature so perhaps my machine just has bum wheels? I placed the machine on a small turntable I happened to have available so it spins around easily now. Regardless, the coffee is really good and I do like that the water tank is removable not to mention the ease of use overall. I recommend it!'),
(6676, 5, 1, 3, '2015-10-20', 'Could have been great - carafe is horrible. This could have been my favorite coffee maker ever. The removable water tank - genius. It makes it to breeze to clean. Then they go and provide the absolute worst Carafe I\'ve ever owned. Folks, you can\'t get the water out of the Carafe; I have to quite violently shake the carafe for a minute and there\'s still a puddle of water in it...seriously one of the stupidest designs i\'ve ever seen. If you don\'t mind watery coffee, then this thing is a buy - otherwise wait until someone over at Hamilton Beach takes their head out of their you know what and designs a simple and easy to wash carafe.'),
(6677, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-10', 'Great investment! Small items cook beautifully in this AND ... Great investment!  Small items cook beautifully in this AND you don\'t have to heat the whole house by turning on the oven.'),
(6678, 7, 3, 5, '2016-02-20', 'I don\'t drink coffee so I got this to drink hot cocoa and tea.....The water is nice and hot and it makes it fast. I just love it.'),
(6679, 12, 1, 2, '2016-08-29', 'The concept is great, hopefully it will one day be improved I feel this toaster/toaster oven is dangerous. The waffles, bread can fall down between the grill onto the toaster oven part and then you can not get it out. Its also hard to clean. If you don\'t use the toaster and toast your bread in the toaster oven it will not be evenly toasted. Stay away from this product.  The concept is great, hopefully it will one day be improved.'),
(6680, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-10', 'Five Stars makes great coffee and easy to program'),
(6681, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'We actually love this! Takes up very little space in the ... Burned through 2 toaster ovens before purchasing just a toaster. We actually love this! Takes up very little space in the kitchen. Toasts thick and thin slices perfectly!'),
(6682, 7, 3, 2, '2016-12-30', 'My second one just died. First one lasted one year. This one, 5 months. Will buy another with warranty and file for future return. Best you can hope for a this price point.'),
(6683, 3, 1, 5, '2016-09-07', 'i love this it works like a big oven and i ... i love this it works like a big oven and i live alone so this is the right size i can bake a regular cake , bake chicken its great.'),
(6684, 5, 1, 3, '2014-02-08', 'Filter overflows I have found that the basket filter overflows leaving grounds in the basket and in the coffee. I do not make my coffee abnormally strong, so I don\'t know why this happens. I never had this problem with coffee makers that use cone filters. It does make a decent cup of coffee. Have found if I gently pack the coffee in the filter it minimizes the overflow. Looks nice and is not oversized so fits under the cabinets even when placed on the pull-out tray we put it on. I do leave it pulled out while brewing since the steam vent is on top. I found in the past that the steam damages the underside of my cabinet. I may buy this again, especially for the price, although may go back to one using a cone filter. We seem to need a new coffeemaker at least every 2 years since we make a LOT of coffee at our house. Got tired of paying $100+ every year or two.'),
(6685, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Awesome small appliance! I am in love with this Keurig 2.0 K200! I love that it has a touch screen that is easy to navigate and a very clear screen that is easy to see. It also has the options of making a carafe and a single cup! I received this product free for testing and would definetly recommend this product if you are looking! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!!'),
(6686, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-18', 'Does what it\'s supposed to do. I can now cook leftover pizza and keep it crispy.'),
(6687, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Black and Decker is the best maker of oven toaster Black and Decker is the best maker of oven toaster! it lets me have a decent and well toasted bread in just a few seconds!'),
(6688, 4, 1, 5, '2016-12-07', 'great easy to use; looks good; perfect size for my home.'),
(6689, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', 'Five Stars Works great! Thank You!'),
(6690, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-08', 'better this time I had owned a previous model of this blender by Hamilton Beach. After about 4 years of use, I finally threw away..it was pretty gross. The previous model was very difficult to clean underneath the blades. This model however is slightly different.. the top is larger, and I have yet to have any difficulties cleaning it. So far so good, I\'ve only used and washed it twice since receiving it. This blender is perfect for the price.'),
(6691, 5, 1, 1, '2017-01-01', 'Not Worth the Money Less than a year old, the front panel/plate that covered the control buttons fell off of the unit and the filter holder clogged, not allowing the coffee to flow. Additionally, it took 30 minutes to brew a pot of coffee. The control buttons went from black to grey. I emailed Hamilton Beach who responded that I needed to take pictures of the unit, cut the electrical cord in half and then send them $12.00 to cover the cost of sending me a new unit. Instead, I went to Costco and bought a new Mr. Coffee for $25.00. Overall, a very poor product. Additionally, Hamilton Beach did not handle my customer service inquiry very well.'),
(6692, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-01', 'Worst toaster oven ever Worst toaster oven ever. It is really hard to figure out the right setting and I have burnt more toast because it wasn\'t toasted enough on the first toast and I tried to toast it for a second round and next thing I know the toast is burnt and I end up leaving hungry for work or late. So annoying. I hope the thing dies soon. Would give it no stars if that was an option.'),
(6693, 4, 1, 5, '2017-01-09', 'Five Stars Love it, perfect size, works great.'),
(6694, 7, 3, 5, '2016-07-23', 'I bought this coffee-maker because I found I was making a whole pot of coffee, only to throw out half, when the rest of the household wakes up (two hours later), and it\'s cold by then ....Then I would brew another cup of coffee..... Honestly I thought I\'d just use this for one or two cups, before everyone else woke up, but now everyone at home uses it! It makes a great cup of coffee ...and is super convenient and versatile! It\'s also super fast to brew a cup! There is no water reservoir on this machine, which makes is very compact! You just fill you coffee cup with cold water, dump it into the machine, pop in the K-cup and hit the brew button! In just a couple of minutes, your coffee is ready! It takes a LOT more time to setup my full-pot machine, get it ready, and then a long time to brew..... I\'ve read some reviews on here, and folks said they got a \"plastic taste\" ...Well yes, if you don\'t follow the instructions, and prepare the machine, you will - but that can happen with any coffee-maker. You need to follow the instructions, and wash all the removable parts in hot soaping water -- rinse and let them dry. Then run the brewer a few times, just brewing water through the machine..... I\'ve been the owner of several coffeehouses, and worked with a LOT of coffee machines - not to mention having owned a couple dozen machines over the years, at home ....You have to clean and prepare them - not use them right out of the box! People have also said their machine stopped working. They had build up on the puncture needle, in the lid -- well yes, if you don\'t maintain your machine, it can get clogged.... Again, reading the instructions, you need to regularly clean the bottom of the lid, the rubber seal, and the needle (use a paperclip to go thru the eye of the needle, and knock out any coffee grounds stuck in there).... I have also used the gold filter, for loose coffee brewing, and it works and tastes great! I had a Keurig in the past, and used an \"adapter\" to use my own coffee, instead of the K-cups, but it was very messy and difficult to setup, as well as clean... This one is great! You just replace the K-cup holder with the gold mesh brew basket, scoop in a couple tablespoons of coffee, and voila! Some reviews on here said the had to \"bang the grounds out\". After brewing with the gold mesh basket, all you have to do is take it to the sink, run water in it, turn it upside, then run water backwards, through the gold mesh .....The grounds go down the garbage disposal! Rinse it well, and air dry..... I Just LOVE this machine! ....As I said, I have owned a Keurig before, and honestly, when I went to Walmart, I had planned on getting another one -- but then I found this little machine there! ....I saved a LOT of money! ....and it\'s more versatile and compact to boot! Can\'t recommend it more.............!'),
(6695, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-28', 'Great toaster in a small space This toaster is nice looking and has all the functions we need. Our counter space is extremely limited and it\'s very compact. It toasts nicely, with extra time for bagels, which we eat a lot. The \"cancel\" feature is useful as well. We bought a matching coffee maker by Cuisinart and are all set!'),
(6696, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(6697, 5, 1, 5, '2016-10-22', 'LOVE IT  NICE  NICE  TELL  SYNCHRONY BANK  STOP  BULLING  AMAZON CUSTORMERS I WOULD BUY IT  ITS LOOK S  NICE ILOVE IT  BUT  AM NOT SHOPPING ON AMAZON FOR NOW  TELL  AMAZON  TO TELL  SYNCHRONY  BANK  STOP BULLING  AMAZON  CUSTOMERS  ITS NOT YOUR  FAULT  COFFEE MAKE  LOOK VERY NICE  IT SAD  NO HOLLY DAY  BUSNESS  SORRY.'),
(6698, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', '5 stars Prepares my post-workout protein shake! Easy to clean as well and it does not retain any smell. Thanks HB!'),
(6699, 5, 1, 2, '2015-08-17', 'it made good coffee. (The only reason I\'m willing to give ... When this was working, it made good coffee. (The only reason I\'m willing to give it 2 stars.) Today, however, it just wouldn\'t turn on. We haven\'t had it for very long, and in that time, we have only used it about 15 times, because we usually drink hot tea. (Side note: the electronic teapot we have - different brand - is still going strong after thrice-daily use!) The coffeepot was immaculately clean, and has just been sitting unplugged for a couple of months. It will NOT turn on. Very disappointed. Very. I spent more money than I should have on this one, because of the decent reviews, and knowing that it should have lasted a while, considering how seldom we use it - for company or the occasional coffee craving. After reading about the hoops people have been forced to jump through to return or exchange their HB coffee pots, I believe i\'ll chalk this one up experience and just get a new one somewhere. I certainly will not ever buy another hamilton beach product.'),
(6700, 4, 1, 2, '2016-07-14', 'This toaster oven has a tendency to be too hot ... This toaster oven has a tendency to be too hot.  It burns everything unless it is on a low temperature.  I had this same oven before and it did not do this.  Maybe this one is a lemon.'),
(6701, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Easy to use and no clean up! This is an amazing coffee/drink maker. This has made my mornings a lot less hectic for sure. It is so easy to use and takes no time to do and no clean up. Wonderful product! I received this product free to review.'),
(6702, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-21', 'Great coffeemaker! Love this coffeemaker!  It is super easy to fill with both water and coffee, our other one was a real pain.  Makes super hot coffee and keeps it hot plenty long enough to drink the whole pot.  Very easy to program also.'),
(6703, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-23', 'I love it. Efficient, it\'s work great. Just take around 5 minutes in toasting bread.'),
(6704, 3, 1, 4, '2015-05-29', 'but other than that it is nice to look at and the programmed times and temps ... Wish it had 2 racks since it is so big. Can\'t use the convection feature on broil, but other than that it is nice to look at and the programmed times and temps are helpful'),
(6705, 7, 3, 4, '2015-12-29', 'It works great and looks good.'),
(6706, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-25', 'This cute little blender is perfect for what I need This cute little blender is perfect for what I need.  It is strong enough to blend peanut butter and it easily fits in my hand for travel.  I make a smoothie before I leave for work and it is a great size for the amount that I want.  I am very pleased!'),
(6707, 11, 1, 5, '2014-12-03', 'Put food in it! 6 months later and I still have no complaints. That means it\'s a winner! It bakes, it toasts it toasts and bakes! I put food in it! Yay!'),
(6708, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-08', 'It makes coffee Considering the cost, and what it does, this coffee maker is perfect. It doesn\'t have a timer or anything fancy on it. You turn it on; you turn it off. It simply makes coffee, people.'),
(6709, 5, 1, 3, '2016-04-23', '15 months of use Good while it lasted. Only lasted 15 months. The power light turns on, but does not start the process.'),
(6710, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-21', 'It has been the perfect solution for the increase in coffee for the winter ... We ordered this to replace our Keurig for our office lunch room.  It has been the perfect solution for the increase in coffee for the winter months.  The coffee is ready to pour on demand and no one is waiting for their coffee. It\'s not burnt like it would have been sitting on a burner and the auto timer option is perfect to make sure that the coffee pot isn\'t accidentally left on after hours.  The washable/reusable filter is perfect for not having excessive waste and mess in our work space.  Would definitely recommend this.'),
(6711, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-27', 'Four Stars The only problem is that I can\'t fit my small casserole dish inside because the rack isn\'t adjustable.'),
(6712, 2, 1, 4, '2016-06-18', 'Four Stars happy with it.'),
(6713, 7, 3, 2, '2015-11-17', 'Contacted customer service they recommend NOT useing Donut House , Donut Shop or Dunkin Donuts. I was using a box of kcups that said Keurig.....Donut House.....Green Mountain. Customer service recommened using Green Mountain, or Great Value cups. Customer service recommended cleaning unit....I tried vinegar/water solution. Unit will not operate correctly even after cleaning and attempting to run cool water 2-3 times. Also rinsed basket and cleaned nozzle repeatedly. Still not working and Hamilton Beach customer service is closed so this one is going back to Walmart :{'),
(6714, 6, 1, 3, '2015-12-02', 'Nice size-burnt toast Pro:Nice compact size-doesn\'t take up alot of counter space. Con:With regular bread I had to turn the dial down to 1 so it would not be burnt or too well done.'),
(6715, 8, 1, 2, '2014-12-16', 'Not a Hot Product. This coffeemaker worked great for the first few months and even tho it\'s basic it did just as I wanted which was heat water or coffee and keep it hot for a while. Alas, after a few months, that is what it didn\'t do. Now I put water in the thing and it comes out tepid at best. The heating element at the bottom will keep it tepid for a while. I want HOT coffee, not coffee that doesn\'t even steam.'),
(6716, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-28', 'It has all the bells and whistles and it makes great This Hamilton beach coffee make is just what the reviews said. It has all the bells and whistles and it makes great coffee'),
(6717, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-02', '2nd Toaster I\'ve had like this--need I say more 2nd Toaster I\'ve had like this--need I say more? First one, I banged on the counter to get the sliced raisin cinnamon toast out of it--and goofed it up. Searched thru the toasters several times--and finally decided to go with a unit I loved the first time! I give it 5 stars as a toaster and it\'s cool looking too!'),
(6718, 7, 3, 1, '2015-05-14', 'Loved it for the first 3 weeks--loved the flexibility of using a K-cup pack, or using my own coffee grounds. At about 3 weeks, it stopped working--coffee starting squirting out of the top when brewing...making a big mess of coffee everywhere. Disappointed because it was just what I needed in terms of flexibility...I guess I gotta go back to the pricey Keurig machine...sad about that! If you choose to purchase, make sure you save all of the packaging and receipt--I am glad I did after reading some reviews on how it broke soon after purchase so I could return for a full refund.'),
(6719, 12, 1, 5, '2014-01-21', 'working for 5+ years now I have had this combo product in my small apartment for over 5 years and it still works flawlessly. Love it. It does toast so much better than traditional toaster ovens and do not need a separate stand alone toaster. It is fairly small, but in a small apartment that is an asset rather than liability.'),
(6720, 1, 1, 3, '2015-06-03', 'Nice product but the DRM\'s will be its downfall We\'ve used the \"old\" Keurig for many years and its been a reliable, steady workhorse in our kitchen. One of the best things things about it (apart from the fact that it does everything except fill its own water reservoir and drink the coffee for you) is that you can use generic K-cups. We buy ours in bulk at Costco and are happy. But we had the opportunity to test drive the new 2.0 machine. It\'s certainly an upgrade, with sleeker design, more options and features, including a descaler and water filter that come free. The user interface is a nice little LCD - gone are the three buttons and plain old featureless monochrome screen. A big deal? Not really. The big kicker is the fact that (like so many other people have reported) is the absurd need of Keurig to try and force people to use proprietary K-cups. No longer do the generics work. Personally, I think this will be their downfall. There are numerous ways of working around this problem, just search the web (or YouTube), but I think it\'s incredibly short-sighted, as well as arrogant. I might mind less if the proprietary coffee were cheaper or better, but its not. One shouldn\'t have to work around the manufacturer, but if you want a Keurig, you\'ll need to (they took the old model off the market). It\'s a shame because the whole concept is innovative and I have trouble believing that the company will make that much more money on K-cups compared to what they would have done if they\'d left the machine DRM-free.'),
(6721, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Five Stars It come in great condition.'),
(6722, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-20', 'Five Stars Works fine; simple to use.'),
(6723, 3, 1, 3, '2016-09-08', 'It\'s nice and large, but it\'s clunky interface needs work. If we had to do it again, I would get a toaster oven with knobs instead of digital controls. It\'s pretty annoying to turn the convection fan on, or add time while it\'s cooking. Oh and I don\'t think there is a way to adjust the temperature without hitting stop, setting it again, and clicking start. Pretty terrible interface.'),
(6724, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-17', 'Excellent As good a toaster oven as I\'ve ever owned. Toasts beautifully. Bargain price.'),
(6725, 12, 1, 5, '2014-04-13', 'works exactly as expected I needed a toaster oven with a small footprint. This one works perfectly as a combination toaster and toaster oven.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(6726, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-08', 'Overall good value for the features Pro\'s: Front, swing-out coffee filter tray access and short rear water resevoir lid mean easy operation, especially when this coffee maker is positioned under cabinets like mine is. The lighted front display makes for easy reading, night and day, although I agree with others that it\'s on the bright side. It makes a good -- if not great -- pot of coffee. The carafe doesn\'t splash and dribble like the Cuisinart it replaced did. The buttons are clearly marked and operations are straightforward and intuitive: I didn\'t need to read the user manual, but did anyway. Con\'s: Construction is on the cheap quality side, with shiny black plastic sides and top. The Cuisinart looked and felt more solid. It\'s a relatively slow brewer; not a deal-buster, and you can always \"pause and serve\" and remove the glass carafe mid-brew to pour yourself a cup, without it dripping onto the hot warming plate below. This unit does not beep to signal that the brewing cycle is complete -- maybe a negative, maybe not. It\'s also slightly noisier than my last coffee maker, but not obnoxiously so. The power cord is only 24\" long, which seems to be industry standard, but why, I have no clue. With the easy-access design and built-in casters in the base that enable you to easily rotate the unit, it\'s not as big of an issue. A note on the casters: they make swiveling the unit easy, but the slightest touch will move it. The built-in water-filter feature is optional and not included. Bottom line: I\'m a \"function trumps form\" kind of guy. So the user-friendly design and good coffee-brewing capability override the cheap-ish plastic appearance. The Cuisinart it replaced was solid (and cost more than twice as much), but somewhat poorly designed with a hard-to-read display, hard-to-clean faceplate, and hard-to-access internal coffee basket and water resevoir. If this unit gives me 3+ years of dependable service, I\'ll have no regrets.'),
(6727, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-16', 'Four Stars Good but somewhat inconsistent browning'),
(6728, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-18', 'WORKS LIKE A CHARM FOR REAR SOME REVIEWS THAT SAID TOASTING WAS UNEVEN ON BREAD BUT HANE NOT FOUND THAT TO BE THE CASE. WORKS LIKE A CHARM FOR US'),
(6729, 5, 1, 2, '2016-12-19', 'Not so solid. Well, I know that I can\'t really expect too much for less than $40, butI haven\'t even used the thing once and the front plate popped off when I first opened the hinged filter door. And again, I get it: it\'s an inexpensive machine, I can\'t expect perfection. But this is... pretty poor construction. I don\'t know if this is a common experience, but the first time I open it? That doesn\'t seem right. Oh, well. I should have spent more money. It\'s not the end of the world. Presumably, it still works. But, you know. Disappointed. And I get it: people complain about absolutely everything these days. But this one warrants a complaint, right?.'),
(6730, 6, 1, 2, '2014-10-19', 'It\'s a great toaster for the money if you are going to ... The toaster itself in compact and attractive. However, it does NOT toast one slice without burning the inside side. If you turn it down enough to eliminate overtoasting the inside side, the outside side is barely beige. It\'s a great toaster for the money if you are going to toast two slides every time. Otherwise, forget it.'),
(6731, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'The degree of brownness with this Cuisinart works better than any other toaster that I have owned I bought this toaster over a year ago and it is still working well.  The degree of brownness with this Cuisinart works better than any other toaster that I have owned.  I am well pleased with my purchase of this brand.  Good quality.'),
(6732, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'Counter Top Oven I was worried about some of the other reviews stating it was too hot, but I haven\'t had any problems with mine. I have enjoyed using it for a while now. It does get hot, but after all, it\'s an oven!'),
