(6766, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-14', 'Great Toaster Oven for the money Great toaster over. When I moved to my new apartment I needed to get a toaster oven. I saw this one in a store and it looked good quality so I checked if it was on amazon and it was cheaper there. I have been using it for about 8 months now with no problems at all. I use it almost every day for something whether it be toast or heating up a meal. I love not having to heat up the whole oven for 2 slices of pizza or a few pieces of chicken. It says 4 slices of toast but I usually put more in there with no problem. I can fit around 3 slices of pizza with a little overlap and it heats them just fine. The broil setting is probably my favorite because I can throw whatever in there and make it crispy. French fries, chicken, anything fried, all gets back to when it was originally made. Overall I highly recommend getting this toaster oven if you are searching for one.'),
(6767, 12, 1, 4, '2016-03-12', 'Perfect size, but has some cons Like the compact size, easy to use, and works great for heating small items. Kinda easy to burn things so don\'t walk away for too long. The downside is that if you have a larger piece of pizza then it won\'t fit. Also, I\'ve had this for a few months and finally tried to toast a bagel today - my toaster feature doesn\'t seem to be working, only the oven part works. If I had it to do over again then I might buy only a toaster oven that was a little larger than this one. Works fine for now since I\'m not a heavy user anyway.'),
