(6822, 9, 1, 4, '2016-09-25', 'It would be amazing with a re-design! I like this pot because the coffee is hotter than the Cuisinart grind and brew with the metal carafe and I enjoy being able to dispense the coffee straight into my mug. I think the design of the internal bucket has much to be desired in regards to its shape and the hot plate. My other dislike is the fact that I can\'t brew more than 8-9 cups at a time or the grounds overflow in to the coffee bucket. But since most of the time we only need to brew 8-9 cups at a time and we drink them in an hour, the dislikes are not major for me to give it a lower star rating.'),
(6823, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-13', 'We really like it! Much faster and more consistant than our old Toastmaster. We really like it!'),
(6824, 9, 1, 5, '2015-11-14', 'The 12 cup Hamilton Beach Brewstation vs the Cuisinart DCC-3000 Coffee-on-Demand 12 cup: Review by consumer who owned both! I changed from the Hamilton Brew Station to this Cuisinart model when my H B\'s clock no longer worked. I was one of the lucky ones who never had the HB leak but I did have a problem with the screen over the dispenser getting blocked and making the coffee stream VERY slow.  I solved that by using very warm vinegar and a soft brush, repeatedly scrubbing the little screen until the stream was pretty adequate.  I think I have now learned to always run some clear hot water thru any coffeemaker\'s dispenser, into an empty cup, to prevent buildup.  The vinegar cleanings don\'t seem adequate. Both models are easy to program to turn on at a specified time. Both are about 15 inches tall when closed, but need more height (24 inches) to lift the cover on the brewed coffee completely to remove that reservoir for cleaning or to remove the used grounds. That is a consideration if you have wall cabinets over your counter and like to tuck the coffeemaker under the wall cabinet. You would need to pull out the coffeemaker to fully open it for emptying after each cycle.  For the HB, you would have to fully open the coffeemaker to fill the water reservoir too.  But not for the Cuisinart side mounted water reservoir. Comparing the two (both need no carafes, which is what I absolutely prefer), I feel the Cuisinart is made much more sturdily. It is of a squarer shape than the HB, but takes up about the same amount of counter space. The gauge on the Cuisinart is nice but only accurate after about 2 cups has been dispensed.  It\'s nice but not a reason to buy this coffeemaker. The reasons to buy the Cuisinart DCC3000 to me are: 1. It brews 12 very hot cups in 10 minutes, with very little noise or hissing 2. It has a very convenient water reservoir: clearly marked with cups, easily removable to fill at the sink, sits firmly in the machine, doesn\'t leak. With my old HB, I had to use a pitcher to fill the non removable reservoir OR use the empty coffee reservoir to bring clear water to the machine.  The Cuisinart fills like the very easy Keurig. On my Cuisinart, I can see the clear water going down as the coffee brews. 3. It is easy to program, with a nice sized blue LED readout. 4. Very nice touch is the light over the cup which goes on only when you dispense coffee; I like seeing how full my cup is. 5. The Cuisinart has a larger heating plate inside the coffee reservoir which keeps the coffee super hot but does NOT burn coffee even if left on for hours.  I think the actual coffee reservoir in the Cuisinart is of a heavier material, (or maybe is double sided?) than the HB reservoir, also helping to retain the heat. 6. The holes inside the top where the water comes out to spray over the grounds seem to be of a better design, more evenly infusing the grounds 7. If you prefer to take a carafe to the table, it is not hard to remove the entire coffee reservoir (CAREFULLY!  YES, IT IS HOT) and pour the freshly brewed contents into a carafe.  You will be removing this black reservoir for cleaning after every use.  But you can remove it when full.  It has lots of extra room when full.  It does not have the convenient pouring spout that the HB coffee reservoir has, but still works okay. Pour from the corner, maybe using an oven mitt to protect your hand from the steam? 8.  The cord comes stored inside the coffeemaker!  If you don\'t pull gently on the plug, you will not have the full 22 inches!  I measured & that is how long the Cuisinart\'s cord is when extended all the way out. 9. The Cuisinart has a water filter in the clear water carafe, which you can choose to replace or not.  Nice feature. 10. The Cuisinart DCC-300 is easy to find & to research. It is a top choice in the Consumer Reports ratings, but the H B Brewstation is not. The H P Brewstation has various models with subtle differences in name/price (the ultra, summit, plus etc).  I comparison shop & want to know exactly what features I am paying for & which vendor has the best price. The Cuisinart, retailing for $99.99, can easily be bought with sales or coupons, for $80.  The HB price varied with each different confusing model number, but around $60 to $80.   11. The Cuisinart has a 3 year warranty. If I get 3 years of everyday use for my $80, I\'ll consider my purchase a win! What the Hamilton Beach Brew Station does have that the Cuisinart lacks 1. The H B had directions on it for making iced coffee, which worked nicely.  I don\'t know if I can make iced coffee with my Cuisinart.  But considering everything else, I feel this is a small inconvenience for a coffeemaker I feel is of better quality overall. 2. The HB did have a high clearance for me to dispense coffee directly into my tall travel mug.  The Cuisinart definitely does not. Its clearance is 6 or 7 inches with a cup straight up. However, if I wanted to, I could take off the cupholder plate entirely, slide the Cuisinart forward to the edge of my counter, and fill my tall travel mug, then slide the coffeemaker back into its usual place.  The drip grate very easily removes/replaces on both coffeemakers. 3. The HB had an adjustment for coffee strength.  I always had mine set on strong, so really didn\'t use that feature.  I think most of us adjust how much coffee we use when we get a new coffeemaker to fit our tastes.  But good to note. Other helpful tips I can share:  I always kept my HB on a tray with one inch sides because so many reviewers said they awoke to a counter awash with hot coffee.  My HB Brewstation, after 2 and a half years, never did leak. I still use a tray, although the Cuisinart has a feature which supposedly would send any leaked coffee into the little drip tray under the dispenser. Better safe than sorry & the tray allows for easily sliding the coffeemaker forward/backward on my counter. I think the vinegar cleaning once a month if using the unit every day is important. My Cuisinart has a button that says clean but I only have had the unit one week, so can\'t comment on that.  The HB had a clean button that lit if it needed cleaning. . .  until the clock went kaput!'),
(6825, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-25', 'Four Stars a bachelors dream'),
(6826, 5, 1, 2, '2015-02-03', 'I don\'t get the love for this coffee maker... I purchased this pot to replace a late, lamented Black and Decker DCM-2500 SmartBrew. (Damn, that was a great pot...and I do not understand the need to replace it with sub-par redesigns.) So, I went with this pot as a replacement after reading the largely stellar reviews. THIS POT DOES NOT BREW COFFEE HOT ENOUGH! The temperature of the water as heated creates coffee that is a couple notches above lukewarm. I pour it in my cup, and after a couple minutes it\'s lukewarm - and this is a thick-walled ceramic \"diner\" mug I\'ve used for years that kept coffee made in my trusty B&D hot for close to 15-20 minutes (if I hadn\'t chugged it down by then). What happens is, the coffee tastes - I don\'t know - different. More bitter. It\'s almost as if Hamilton Beach is depending on the heating element to finish heating the coffee. Which it does, but that\'s not brewing, that\'s \"cooking\". Two/three days and four disappointing pots later, I returned it and got the Mr. Coffee BVMC-SJX33GT (http://www.amazon.com/Mr-Coffee-BVMC-SJX33GT-Programmable-Coffeemaker/dp/B0047Y0UQO) instead. Now, THAT is a four-star coffee maker. Hot from the start, and the difference is instantly recognizable.'),
(6827, 8, 1, 3, '2016-08-06', '2nd Try So far, so good. The first one was replaced. It didn\'t begin to wear out, just stopped. Didn\'t brew & held the water in the reservoir. The compact size is perfect for my limited counter space.'),
(6828, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-20', 'Five Stars Beautiful even toast.  What can I say . . .'),
(6829, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'Great quick little blender to get the job done Perfect for quick individual smoothies on the go'),
(6830, 5, 1, 1, '2016-02-03', 'Defective on arrival The hotplate was scratched when I received it. It\'s not that big of a deal except I paid full price for a coffeemaker with a defect. UPDATE: There was also an 1/8th inch chip in the hotplate rim. Hamilton Beach wants me to cut the cord and send them a photo before they\'ll send me a replacement. I don\'t want to be without a coffee maker during that time and they won\'t allow me to disable the unit after I receive the new one. That\'s crappy customer service and a waste of my time for this junky appliance.'),
(6831, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-10', 'it is just fine, I like it very much the keurig was the second  one that  I have used,  it is just fine, I like it very much.'),
(6832, 4, 1, 2, '2015-04-13', 'Faulty Element kills an otherwise good toaster. When the oven worked, I liked it.  Then the front heating element started to bend and split.  Finally broke.  No replacement elements available.  Widespread issue if you research it.  Cuisinart will replace if you\'re willing to ship it back to them at your cost plus $10.  I would not buy this oven again.'),
(6833, 12, 1, 5, '2015-06-27', 'Five Stars work good'),
(6834, 1, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'Five Stars we all love this brewing system....just perfect for the three of us....'),
(6835, 12, 1, 1, '2014-12-01', 'Worst Toaster Ever -- Potential Fire Hazard -- Uneven Toasting 1 year old: (1) Leg fell off so it wobbles (2) Caught on fire once_ had to unplug it and swat it with a dish towel (3) Does not toast evenly. Frozen waffles will come out half-done and half semi-frozen, and need to go in for toasting a second time. (4) The \"Oven\" part of the toaster oven broke. The handle no longer works to put it into \"Oven\" mode without great difficulty. ALL IN ALL -- THE WORST TOASTER OVEN I HAVE EVER OWNED. I will not be purchasing another \"Hamilton Beach\" again, that\'s for sure, bro!'),
(6836, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-29', 'Good purchase Works quite well. Very happy with the purchase.  Fill my own k-cups and get an excellent brew.'),
(6837, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'Makes good coffee Practical, fast, makes good coffee, easyclean and a very good price. A good purchase,'),
(6838, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-29', 'Looks great Looks and performs awesome. Looks and cooks like a high end appliance but still affordable. Ordered this for my brothers new house. He thought I spent too much money on him it looked so pro. Would recommend for sure'),
(6839, 4, 1, 1, '2015-07-05', 'Worst toaster oven ever! Besides making very crappy, dried-out toast, this over-priced Cuisinart toaster oven is downright dangerous! After less than a year of use, the heating elements began to distort noticeably, and ultimately the rear element developed a large crack that would glow white hot when the toaster was turned on. (See attached picture.) I threw the Cuisinart in the garbage and replaced it with a Breville BOV650XL, which is an all around  fantastic toaster oven. I feel safer already.'),
(6840, 6, 1, 3, '2014-09-11', 'okay thats all maybe I have not figured the settings yet but toast is  not consistent. The toaster is not bad enough to return BUT not of the quality I expected of a Cuisinart product.'),
(6841, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-29', 'Useful quality The product is really great, the quality is very good for a reasonable price, very happy to have made this choice.'),
(6842, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-30', 'This blender is perfect for the work place and home This blender is perfect for the work place and home. It is an easy way to make yourself a serving or even two for you and someone else.'),
(6843, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-30', 'Five Stars Love this little pot!.'),
(6844, 7, 3, 5, '2014-05-17', 'I have used it for everyday for the past two weeks and love it. I read and follow the directions and have had none of the issues mentioned in other reviews. It is not compatible with Keurug k cups, however, I open them and put them into the filter and problem solved. It heats well and fast, under 2 minutes. I highly recommend this product, small, sleek design and easy to use, minimum clean up and it\'s a bargain.'),
(6845, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-19', 'I love this oven I love this oven.  It\'s my second purchase of this same one.  The ex got to keep the last one.  It saves time and money, from heating up your oven, which always takes forever or having a separate toaster for bread on your counter..  This heats up to 450 degrees in about 3 minutes.  I\'ve cooked everything from fish sticks and pizza\'s to a full stuffed chicken, and lasagna! It\'s the best! I highly recommend this oven to everyone, even families.  I love that it\'s digital, you just set the temperature and cooking time, and as soon as it beeps, insert your food.  Upon completion of cooking, it automatically shuts off.  Amazing value, also compared to similiar convection ovens, with turn knobs.  (most of the more expensive ovens seemed cheaply made to me).'),
(6846, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-20', 'Buy it!  It\'s great! This is a sharp looking toaster oven that I have used several times to cook salmon.  So far so good.  The only annoying thing (I think others have mentioned it, too), is that the labels for the control buttons are written really really small.  I usually spend 5 minutes trying to figure out setting the temp.  I still don\'t know how to make it cook longer than the 30 minute timer.  I guess I\'ll have to read the directions ;)'),
(6847, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'Better than expected PROS: Works quickly and fairly quietly for its size. I own a larger glass blender (Oster) and this little guy does a better job most of the time. Because it\'s a pulse style, stuff doesn\'t get stuck under the blades too easily. I\'ve been able to make shakes, smoothies, and sometimes soups using this blender. It has no problem with ice too. You can also use the unit itself as a cup, which seems lame but I\'ve done it a few times when I\'m too lazy to wash an extra cup and it works nicely. CONS: It doesn\'t have a ton of power. It\'s made for pulsing, which works great for *most* things. This isn\'t a BlendTec so don\'t expect to be able to shred your iPhone. I don\'t see this as a huge con though because this is so inexpensive.'),
(6848, 11, 1, 4, '2014-06-17', 'toaster Added to my collection  for my kitchen . It works well have no complaints thus far...only proble is the cord is too short'),
(6849, 3, 1, 2, '2015-07-06', 'it is very confusing to use/no good. it  is very confusing to use/no good.'),
(6850, 11, 1, 1, '2014-08-16', 'Worst toaster I ever had Worst toaster I ever had ! No instructions with it and very difficult to set it. Toast mode cooks on just one side of the bread. Very dissatisfied !'),
(6851, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-10', 'Five Stars What a fabulous little blender!!'),
(6852, 11, 1, 2, '2014-08-09', 'Two Stars Controlls are a little odd, not user friendly.'),
(6853, 12, 1, 5, '2014-02-28', 'After 3 years works great and still looks new I have had this toaster/oven now for over three years and I still love it!  Great for toast but also for cooking small items.  Takes up minimal space on counter and easy to clean.'),
(6854, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-30', 'Very Happy! Works great and makes a perfect cup of HOT coffee every time.'),
(6855, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-19', 'Five Stars Best little oven that I have had!  Use it daily.'),
(6856, 5, 1, 4, '2015-10-16', 'Good automatic coffee maker. It works well and makes good coffee and is easy to clean.  It does make more noise while brewing than our former one.  I like the feature that is shuts off after 2 hours, in case we forget.  All in all is is satisfactory.'),
(6857, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-24', 'Not only pretty but very efficient. A great replacement for my five year old until. No regrets but lots of smiles.'),
(6858, 4, 1, 1, '2016-02-03', 'Not For Me This oven\'s door did not close tightly and could see inside from edges. Heat escaped. Seemed to toast well but did not like using the oven for the faulty door reason. It also takes up A LOT of counter space - would be great in a corner of a large kitchen. Returned item for refund.'),
(6859, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-23', 'Four Stars Works well and has all the features I was looking for!'),
(6860, 3, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Big upgrade from a normal toaster So far with limited use (toasting and some re-heating), great product.  The printing on it is a bit tough to read and the beeping it makes with every button depression can be a little annoying but I can\'t deny I like the oven so far and would buy it again.'),
(6861, 7, 3, 5, '2015-01-28', 'Great product. Easy to use and fun trying different coffees and teas.'),
(6862, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-09', 'This is a very good basic toaster oven...remember get what you really need..size is perfect... After many years of not using a toaster oven, we opted to get one.  Both wife and son basically asked, \"What took you so long?\"  All I can say is to get one that will address your needs.  Personally, we use it to toast (see pic), warm up with a slight toasted finish and use it to toast / prep Japanese prepared package mochi and will accommodate larger bread slices.  Son said he\'ll use it to warm up some prepackaged pot pies.  Basically a easy to use toaster / oven.  So far the results are good and you need to get used to the settings that will accommodate your tastes.  Again, get what you need and don\'t get something that you may end being overkill.'),
(6863, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-26', 'Five Stars The perfect coffee maker at a reasonable price. Love the digital display!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(6864, 5, 1, 4, '2017-01-09', 'Made coffee, piece fell off, still makes coffee We have a Keurig also but wanted the \'old school\' coffee maker because I now drink 3+ cups per day. Got this from asking Alexa to order it and so it cost just over $20 - pretty good deal. Also ended up purchasing the reusable metal filter that is nice. I set the timer at night for 7am and by 7:10am there is a hot pot of coffee ready. LCD display is very bright which might be a problem if it was in my bedroom but it is in the kitchen. Been using it about two weeks and noticed the top front panel was loose. Looked a little closer and saw that it was no longer attached - see photo. The core function still works - coffee making - and my boys think it looks cool without the panel so I don\'t plan to return a $20 coffee maker because of this defect.'),
(6865, 8, 1, 4, '2016-10-01', 'Really good budget product. I just got the coffee maker today which came to days before it was supposed to. I made a fresh batch of coffee and I\'m so happy. There\'s no bells and whistles to this thing but it makes a damn good cup of coffee.'),
(6866, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-08', 'Exceeds expectations. Works great and yes the top does get hot but not in any way a fire hazard. Toasts perfectly and is a great value for money spent.'),
(6867, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', '... and made a few different things already and I love it. This is my first toaster oven and ... I bought mine from Walmart but I\'ve had it s few days now and made a few different things already and I love it. This is my first toaster oven and I consulted with a friend of mine who has had them before I purchased mine. She suggested that I get one with a temperature control because it makes a huge difference. I have burned a few things so far, some toast and frozen waffles, but now I know what exact setting to use for perfect toasting it\'s an amazing toaster oven. I don\'t regret my purchase at all.'),
(6868, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-07', 'Very happy with this product Fast shipping. Very happy with this product. It\'s a bit bigger than I expected but still looks and works great.'),
(6869, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-07', 'Compact yet powerful. Though I already had smoothie makers, thought will give it a try as it looks compact and easy carry around cup.'),
(6870, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Five Stars THIS IS A RELAY GOOD COFFEE MACHINE FOR THE PRICE IT MAKES GOOD COFFEE.'),
(6871, 11, 1, 5, '2015-04-07', 'Five Stars Works great and at a great price.'),
(6872, 9, 1, 4, '2016-11-03', 'I like it. Handy way to make coffee for someone who lives alone, but also has occasional guests.'),
(6873, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-26', 'Love my new Keurig Love my new Keurig.  My only issue is that it is still not quite tall enough for my travel mug, but I can put the coffee in the carafe and transfer it if I need to. I know some mention the noise, and the noise is different from my k45...but it is not any noisier than other coffee pots I have had.'),
(6874, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-14', 'Fantastic coffee pot! This is our third purchase of this coffee pot.  The first was for us several years ago and we loved it so we got one as a gift a couple of years ago, and have just purchased the third for our cabin.  Our original still works great.  I hope this model is still being made when our original finally goes as we would purchase another without hesitation!'),
(6875, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Love it. Just the right size for what I ... Love it.  Just the right size for what I need.'),
(6876, 10, 1, 1, '2016-04-02', 'One Star Received broken'),
(6877, 12, 1, 1, '2016-06-17', 'Fire Hazard! I purchased one of these about 8 years ago (toaster #1) and after it was too filthy to look at anymore (but still functioning) , I tossed it and bought a new one just like it (toaster #2) That was two years ago. A few months ago the front door latch broke ((used a piece of tape to keep it closed) and recently one of the legs broke off. I figured \'no big deal\' because I do use it every day and it lasted two years, so I bought another one (toaster #3). Less than a month after buying toaster #3, the mechanism that makes the toast pop up stopped working and nearly set my house on fire. There was nothing next to the toaster to obstruct the lever, so this is clearly a design flaw. Also, on toaster #3, the pan was warped and barely fit into the slot.  In the first photo, you can see the outline of where the blazing slice of toast landed after I manually ejected it. The burn mark is permanent. The second is a pic of my poor toast. I would like to note that I compared the info on the bottom of both toaster ovens #2 and #3 and they have identical manufacturer info, and were both made in 2014. I\'m guessing the old design of toaster #1 was changed and toasters #2 and #3 are supposed to be the \'new and improved\' model.'),
(6878, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-30', 'really good. make my smoothies everyday really good.make my smoothies everyday. Drink it directly from the container. Easy to clean'),
(6879, 5, 1, 1, '2016-11-27', 'Not happy that I\'ve missed the return window Don\'t buy this. Program timer button broke and front panel is falling off after two months of gentle use! Not happy that I\'ve missed the return window.'),
(6880, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-05', 'Very nice. Attractive looking Very nice.  Attractive looking.  Works as expected.'),
(6881, 11, 1, 5, '2014-04-23', 'Does the job It does the job and is a little smaller but easier to use than the Oster one it replaced. I like that outside it\'s smaller. I do wish it had twin heating elements on top and bottom though. This one uses one big element for top and one for bottom. I haven\'t noticed uneven heating but it\'s something to keep in mind.'),
(6882, 12, 1, 5, '2016-01-25', 'Five Stars Fits our needs to a tee!'),
(6883, 2, 1, 3, '2016-04-20', 'Dies with light use I bought this about 14 months ago. After making toast 3-4 times a week, the heating lower element died. The two year warranty requires that I send the plug back and a check for $7.50. After they receive that, it will take 7-10 days to get a replacement. So with return shipping costs of $1-2 dollars I am out about $9 and no toaster for 10-14 days. I had been disappointed with B&D in the past and had tried them again. And again I was disappointed. Easier to buy a different brand.'),
(6884, 11, 1, 5, '2014-06-24', 'GREAT I LOVE THIS SO MUCH IM HERE BACK FOR A 2ND ONE! MAYBE A 3RD ONE IN THE NEAR FUTURE! WORKS GREAT LIKE ADVERTISED AND HIGHLY RECOMMENDED TO FAMILY AND FRIENDS. SO FAR SO GOOD. NO CONS YET.'),
(6885, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'Great coffee maker So far I love it. It is simple and easy to use. It swivels so you can put the water in the back. Has programmable features so I can make coffee at night.'),
(6886, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-03', 'Replaced our old one with this and couldn\'t be happier! My other, bigger, Black and Decker toaster oven just quit working after about a year. It stopped heating. I went with this smaller one because my parents have it and I love using it when I\'m visiting. I think I\'ll probably need a bigger one eventually because we pretty much use this instead of the regular oven ( just 2 of us). But for now this one is great! It toasts very evenly, performs better than my other one. Will probably go with the digital extra wide later but loving this until we outgrow it! This one just feels sturdier, too.'),
(6887, 12, 1, 3, '2015-04-15', 'Three Stars The toast falls down and get stuck'),
(6888, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Five Stars It\'s a great product, goes great with my kitchen Decour very happy with it.'),
(6889, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-10', 'Great coffee maker Slight plastic taste for first few brews, but then goes away. Love the way it fills. No spills, dribbles. Definitely recommend.'),
(6890, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-01', 'Pleased with purchase Great basic toaster at bargain price. Replaced Dualit which quit. Works perfectly so far.'),
(6891, 7, 3, 4, '2014-10-22', 'It is great if you just want one cup of coffee. I make it right before I leave for work in the morning for on the go. I wish it held more water for the 16 oz to go mugs.'),
(6892, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-14', 'Five Stars Excellent toasting and crumb tray.'),
(6893, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-22', 'If I had space, I would get two. This is a great toaster oven. I can use my 9x13 flat sided pans. A 12\" pizza fits and cooks up nicely.'),
(6894, 2, 1, 3, '2016-01-20', 'the B&D toaster oven controls are a bit clunky and not particularly easy to use or intuitive in their use While a decent appliance, the B&D toaster oven controls are a bit clunky and not particularly easy to use or intuitive in their use. For the price not bad, but some simply redesign would make this a really good toaster oven as opposed to just an adequate.one.'),
(6895, 6, 1, 1, '2015-09-21', 'Hated it! I really wanted to like this. Its just a poor quality product.  Barely browns toast on the highest setting.  Returned it.'),
(6896, 6, 1, 4, '2015-07-11', 'Some unevenness in toasting but it seems to be getting better. Like the ability to raise the toast for ... It works; It toasts! Some unevenness in toasting but it seems to be getting better. Like the ability to raise the toast for easy removal. Hope it lasts for years.'),
(6897, 11, 1, 5, '2015-02-01', 'Toasts well and is cheap Good, cheap toaster oven which does what it says.  It may not be the greatest or last the longest but it is just a good, inexpensive toaster.  I have had three of these over the past 20 years and still haven\'t spent what it would cost to buy some of the fancy ones.  I just wanted something just to toast bread and bagels and occasionally heat a slice of pizza.  This works.  If you want to do more, buy one of the more expensive ovens.  If you just want a good toaster, buy this.'),
(6898, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-23', 'Five Stars Works great as both toaster and toaster oven. Amazing!!!.'),
(6899, 10, 1, 5, '2015-08-05', 'It is quieter and it works just fine for protein shakes I have purchased several h.b.personal blenders..  I used to have a magic bullet but it was too LOUD and too hard to clean and it sometimes leaked all over and made a mess in the kitchen.  So I found this at walmart and switched.  It is quieter and it works just fine for protein shakes, smoothies, coconut yogurt and coconut milk based drinks. The blender is small and light enough that I have taken it in my suitcase on several vacations.  When I forget to take one, it is inexpensive enough to pick on up at the local walmart for breakfast in the hotel room.  As I learn more about nutrition, my diet changes but this blender is a constant over the years.'),
(6900, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-15', 'So far we\'re loving it. Cant get enough toast ... So far we\'re loving it. Cant get enough toast. Toasts fast, it is toasting a bit uneven at times but I attribute that to not really being broken in yet. Either way, a little uneven toast never killed anyone.'),
(6901, 2, 1, 3, '2016-07-30', 'We like it because of the price and size I buy this toaster once every 9 months. We like it because of the price and size. But after a while the heating element breaks down and no longer heats food properly.'),
(6902, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-09', 'Good product but not perfect Coffee maker works well but doesn\'t give you an option to make 1-4 cups with bold setting.  It does keep the coffee hot.  I like the easy rolling feature on the bottom.'),
(6903, 8, 1, 3, '2016-05-18', 'this is a tiny coffee maker- not full size When I purchased this I did not realized it is not a full size coffee pot so that was a huge disappointment. It turned out to be the exact mini version of the one I was trying to replace. In the end we threw this item away because it doesn\'t stop dripping if you take the pot out to pour coffee before the entire pot is done brewing and it doesn\'t have an automatic shut off.'),
(6904, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-02', 'GREAT! This little thing works AMAZINGLY well. Blends fast, has good power, crushes ice well. Love it for morning smoothies.'),
(6905, 7, 3, 1, '2016-08-13', 'I got this item as a gift from my daughter. It worked about a month. Got it working again. It stopped pumping. Got another...stopped pumping...3rd time?? Yup. Stopped working. Just a terrible unit. Too bad because I really liked it.'),
(6906, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-06', 'Great coffee maker with most of the common features you\'d need. I love this maker so far.  We\'ve had it a few months now.  So a few things I like - I like that you can remove the water reservoir to fill the water.  The pause and serve function works well, so you can pull the pot out while you are still brewing.  The temperature setting for the hot plate is nice, as I sometimes leave the coffee for a long time on the burner, and it keeps it from tasting burned.  You also have the strength setting, which I don\'t use because I only make \"a lot\" at a time, but apparently you can set it for \"small, medium, and large\" amount of coffee.  The timer works as expected.  Also, quirky, but useful for some (not me) is it has little wheels under it that allow you to rotate it, so you can fill the water more easily, I guess.  Where my coffee maker sits I just have to pull it out and push it back to do that task, but in the right place it could be very helpful.  So far I love it.  It is tough to tell, because in general most of them are fine with me, but deteriorate badly over time.  We\'ll see how this one does, but so far so good.'),
(6907, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-19', 'toasts makes great toast.  no complaints.'),
(6908, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-22', 'Great coffee maker for the price Decent enough. BOLD coffee option is cool. Makes for some tasty coffee, but it takes quite a bit longer. It\'s worth the wait though. I just wish it was 14 cups!'),
(6909, 5, 1, 3, '2014-10-29', 'MADE OF LIES AND NOT GOOD At current I own five cofee makers to save time.  I must express feeling for this machine: I do not love.  I do NOT LOVE AT ALL/ dOes not have off switch for turning it not on--which shows they know NOT ANYTHING.  Had to shut power off in hole house in order to stop the cofee flood.  Cat nearly drowned in the beans and the cofee was every where and not on the beach.  couldn\'t even tell if toilet was filled with coffee or the bowel movement I THINK I had birthed.  Mr. hamilton needs to contact Paris Hamilton in order to correctly make cofee--she is good at that.  I need mention: does not come with 12 cups and all the steel is stainy.  Says \"DIGITAL\" but cant connect to internet?  The world wibe wed is eassy to get at from my Coffee Beanwright 2309 and my Espexxo Caffinator A2357.'),
(6910, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'Happy with my first Keurig! Just received my first Keurig coffee maker and am very happy with it. The water gets nicely hot, the coffee is delicious and of course it\'s very easy to use. The coffee maker also looks very sleek on my kitchen counter. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(6911, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-13', 'Five Stars VERY PLEASED - WAS WHAT I HOPED IT WOULD BE...DELIVERY WAS ON TIME...'),
(6912, 11, 1, 5, '2016-01-03', 'works great, fits bigger items that it looks like it ... No problems, works great , fits bigger items that it looks like it would. Great product'),
(6913, 12, 1, 1, '2017-01-08', 'Toaster part works well. Oven part doesn\'t be work ... Toaster part works well. Oven part doesn\'t be work well. Bra uses the top burners are so close to the tray it burns the top of everything. Also door/tray hooks are poorly made. Thrown away after about three months.'),
(6914, 6, 1, 4, '2016-02-01', 'strongly satisfied Amazing product at the reasonable cost not bad at all i am strongly satisfied with it'),
(6915, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'Five Stars Great'),
(6916, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-21', 'Consistent, excellent toaster. We\'ve had two toasters plus this one during our 50 years marriage. My husband has been griping about our last one for probably 20 years, pretty much from when I bought it. I finally had enough and bought this Cuisinart CPT-142. We BOTH like it. It is consistent in the color of the toast. It doesn\'t suck all the moisture out which leaves the bread worth eating. Toasting one, two, three or four slices doesn\'t matter. They all come out the same. I would recommend it to a friend or even a stranger.'),
(6917, 1, 1, 5, '2015-10-04', 'The bestest 2.0 It is a awesome coffee maker, just make sure you get the Kcups or it won\'t work'),
(6918, 8, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'but this also means that you cannot remove the carafe while brewing like many models that use a sealed filter unit with ... I chose this simple coffee brewing design because it can also be used for tea or boiled water. It is one of the only units where the water can pass directly into the carafe when you remove the cupcake filter basket, but this also means that you cannot remove the carafe while brewing like many models that use a sealed filter unit with a plunger to hold water from flowing into the carafe. I am able to use this carafe system for heating ramen noodles or tea bags. Using this coffee system to also heat water is a great advantage for many small but casual alternative uses where you want steamed water.'),
(6919, 12, 1, 4, '2015-04-07', 'Four Stars Looks great, and works great.  I was disappointed that there was no timer on the oven portion.'),
(6920, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-20', 'Among the best toaster-overns I\'ve ever owners This Black and Decker is vastly superior to toaster overs at double and triple the price. For example, I had purchased a Hamilton Beach toaster oven, also via Amazon about a year ago. It was somewhat larger but all of the warnings in the reviews of the Hamilton Beach turned out to be true: very hot, blue \"on\" light nearly impossible to see, toast seems to go from totally undone to totally overdone in a matter of seconds, etc. No such problems with this Black and Decker. Another example that higher price doesn\'t necessarily mean higher quality.'),
(6921, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-24', 'The best coffee maker for the price! I was upset when my Calphalon 12 Cup Glass Carafe broke and I couldnt replace it due to Calphalon discontinuing their electrics line, so I looked online for reviews.  This model kept getting great reviews and the price was very reasonable.  I have used it for  a few weeks now and I love it!  So easy to use, clean and its compact so it fits all of my needs.  If you are in the market for a coffee maker, and all you want to do is make coffee, buy this one!'),
(6922, 12, 1, 1, '2014-06-23', 'Did not like it bagels kept getting stuck.  only one toast fit at a time.  Gave it away already and went and got a new one at the store.'),
(6923, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-17', 'Great value for such a fine countertop oven... I brought this to replacing an older Toaster oven with dials.  I\'m not one to read manuals and it\'s quite user friendly.  I am using this to broil all my meats and maybe lasagna in the future.  For tonight, I had baked pork chops, broiled 4 Atlantic salmon steaks and 1 cod fish for dinner.  They all came out moist and tasty.  Both my girl friend and I had a wonderful romantic dinner together.  All oven gets HOT so wear gloves!  Toasting bread only?  Buy a toaster!  I also wrap the pan with excessive aluminum foil to keeping any cooked oil or juice from from dripping as I hate to clean!  Also, there\'s a tray on the bottom of which it can slide out; I also wrap that part as well. When it gets dirty, I\'ll just slide it out and toss the foil. Enjoy!.'),
(6924, 5, 1, 1, '2015-09-29', 'I am disappointed. I bought this unit 3 months back. Used it once a day and kept it clean. The burner completely rusted it out. I called the support, they agreed to replace it but they wanted me to cut the electrical cord, and then send a picture to prove to them I have the unit, and then after 10 business days they\'d send a replacement. So for 10+ days no coffee machine plus I pay $14.99 for shipping. I offered to give my CC no. so they can charge me for the new coffeemaker until I send them a photo but no luck. I understand sometimes any product could fail but please don\'t make it too difficult to get a replacement. I am disappointed.'),
(6925, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-07', 'So far so good. Toasts everything just right So far so good.  Toasts everything just right.  Faster then any others we have had.  No complaints.'),
(6926, 7, 3, 2, '2015-11-08', 'Did not work well for me. Did not brew all the water poured in machine, so coffee came out too strong.'),
(6927, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-24', 'Five Stars good'),
(6928, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-03', 'Basic and convenient It does basic blending, such as smoothies. It can\'t hold up to larger or tougher items. However, if you want some ice, fruit, and milk/water this is perfect. Easy to take on the go.'),
(6929, 3, 1, 5, '2016-10-18', 'Five Stars very good product.'),
(6930, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-07', 'HighTech Toastser Three dials seems a lot for a basic toaster. But I can always get my teenager to operate it for me'),
(6931, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-20', 'I haven\'t had it for very long but so far it\'s been perfect. My son and fianc use it every morning ... I don\'t have any white appliances in my kitchen but when I saw the reviews on this product, I was convinced enough. I haven\'t had it for very long but so far it\'s been perfect. My son and fianc use it every morning and sometimes in the evenings. Our last toaster only lasted a year, and I can see this one going a long way.'),
(6932, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-09', 'This is a wonderful small appliance for a single person I hardly ever use my regular oven anymore.  This is a wonderful small appliance for a single person!'),
(6933, 2, 1, 1, '2016-10-22', 'A dreadful product! This is a dreadful product, but there\'s no real competition.  For years I had the General Electric Toast-R-Oven which was small and well designed, but it finally wore out.  GE\'s small appliance business was bought by Black & Decker,  and I expected they would continue with decent quality.  Wrong!  This toaster oven is much bigger but does much less than the GE.  You have to set three dials for every piece of toast;  the markings on the dials are almost illegible, the toast doesn\'t pop out when done;  the inside of the oven is too low (short from top to bottom) to bake things that fit into the smaller GE; it has only 2 heating elements, one on top and one on the bottom (the smaller GE had 4 heating elements);  the metal exterior gets extremely hot; and there\'s more but life is to short to cover it all...  Take a look at reviews that tell of fires with the B&D,  of the handle melting, and of the glass door exploding! Anyway, I returned this oven, scoured the internet and was lucky to find a used old GE Deluxe Toast-R-Oven.  Now I\'m content, but I don\'t understand why Black & Decker doesn\'t copy the classic GE design.'),
(6934, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'the best part of this is the ability to take the ... the best part of this is the ability to take the water reservoir to the faucet just love that !!!!'),
(6935, 1, 1, 1, '2016-03-08', 'Defective Brewer was defective. I contacted Keurig three times and they finally sent me a replacement brewer.'),
(6936, 7, 3, 4, '2014-10-07', 'We had unwittingly moved the coffee maker around on the counter and later discovered that it would no longer make a full cup even though we were adding the same amount of water as before when we did get a full cup. My wife (had to be her, darn) noticed a very slight slant backward in the pot. I found a small rubber pad to place underneath the back end and the coffee maker returned to making the normal size cup. It now has a very slight slant in the forward direction. This troubleshooting point it not listed in the accompanying manual.'),
(6937, 5, 1, 1, '2016-11-29', 'Cute but crap Very disappointed in the craftsmanship and overall shoddy assembly of this coffee maker. It\'s cute, sure. Doesn\'t take up much counter space and is efficient. But the front plate disconnects EVERY time I remove or add a coffee filter. The handle on the pitcher seems disconnected so when I wash it, it seems as though water gets trapped inside of it. The glass itself is paper thin. It\'s not durable at all, in any way, shape, or form. Very disappointing purchase. I honestly expect more from Hamilton Beach.'),
(6938, 5, 1, 2, '2016-05-17', 'Two Stars almost one year to date the automatic button is broke'),
(6939, 4, 1, 5, '2015-09-14', '... had this for over a year now and really love it. It\'s so easy to clean which is ... I\'ve had this for over a year now and really love it. It\'s so easy to clean which is my usual complaint about toaster ovens. The bottom tray slides out for easy cleaning. It works well and looks nice too.'),
(6940, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'Five Stars good'),
(6941, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-22', 'Love it!! Love it...coffee tastes great and stays hot.'),
(6942, 7, 3, 5, '2015-12-09', 'I am really enjoying my purchase and would recommend this to anyone! It took me a couple of days to get the right amount of coffee to make a cup, but when I did I am so happy to have this coffee maker. This is perfect for me as I don\'t always like to make a whole pot for just once person.'),
(6943, 6, 1, 1, '2014-10-24', 'Not worth the effort to send it back Great toaster if you want one side burnt and the other side white. Into the trash it went.'),
(6944, 2, 1, 1, '2015-12-29', 'Third time use it, the auto timer stopped working ... Third time use it, the auto timer stopped working, and my bread burned inside, and triggered the fire detector. It can be quite dangerous. I am throwing it out to the trash now!'),
(6945, 3, 1, 5, '2014-07-24', 'this is the best ever! I bought serveral convection ovens in the past, this is the best ever!'),
(6946, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-03', 'Itu2019s all about the measurement; brew selection & type of coffee (Mild, Medium Dark & Bold). Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffee Maker, 49997, Black If you are new to using this type of coffee maker it will take a few tests to get that cup of coffee you are accustomed to, You have the option to brew using your ground coffee or using the K-cup Packs, the key to making a cup using the ground coffee is using the right measurements and selecting the bold brew, if you select regular it brews very fast and you will get a cup of what I call coffee flavored water. If you plan to use the ground filter you need to take out the K-cup filter holder, I used two large table spoons and a half of ground coffee and 10 ounces of cold filter water(if you close the top the water will settle down into the coffee maker) select bold brew. When using the K-cups I found the brand that I brought came in mild, medium, dark and bold; so I place the K-cup holder back into coffee maker, it snaps right into it, donu2019t remove the top cover on your k-cup, once you close the top of coffee maker it will punch a hold it, since my coffee is already dark roasted coffee I measured out a little over 10 ounces of cold filter water, selected bold brew and got a strong cup of coffee. So the key to FlexBrew is measurement, brew selection and type of coffee (Mild, Medium, Dark and Bold).'),
(6947, 2, 1, 2, '2015-04-02', 'Bad product returned a piece of junk'),
(6948, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-10', 'Works great and perfect for smaller kitchens Purchased for my father and he loves it. Works great and perfect for smaller kitchens.Smaller toaster ovens have minimal preheating times, and easily illuminate the need for a toaster AND a microwave (if you are trying to reduce radio active waves in your home).'),
(6949, 7, 3, 5, '2015-04-27', 'I decided to try this coffee maker. I own a Kuerig coffee brewer, but it has been giving me a little trouble. I got this one to see if it was as good as the one I have. Well, I am pleased to say it is better than the one I have. It allows me to brew one cup of coffee at a time. However, this coffee maker even allows you to use fresh ground coffee! So, you can use ANY of the K-cups AND fresh ground coffee as well. That is a plus to me, because sometimes one is on sale while the other is not. Now I can buy either one. I took my K-cup and followed the directions and made a cup of coffee in less than two minutes. When it comes to the fresh grounds, all you need to do is put three tablespoons of fresh ground coffee in the machine and fill the water reservoir with water and brew away. This coffee maker allows you to have your coffee u201cRegularu201d or u201cBoldu201d when you brew it. The one thing I do not like about this brewer is that you have to rinse out the K-cup holder after each use. However, I love that I am able to use a small cup or a tall travel tumbler with this coffee maker. This brewer has a shelf that can be put in a higher position or lower position based on the size of the cup, mug, or tumbler you are using.'),
(6950, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-22', 'Great! Awesome toaster. Works very well after a couple of weeks. Our old toaster\'s crumb tray had fallen off and this one doesn\'t make a huge mess.'),
(6951, 5, 1, 5, '2015-07-10', 'Great inexpensive drip coffee maker! Excellent automatic drip coffee maker.  Flawless construction.  Works very well.  Easy to setup and brew coffee and easy to clean.  You won\'t be disappointed, particularly at this price.'),
(6952, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-15', 'I just received the coffee maker on the 31st of ... I just received the coffee maker on the 31st of May and not even 2 weeks later the metal around the carafe is rusting!!!'),
(6953, 5, 1, 4, '2015-11-06', 'Plenty of options and incredibly easy to clean It has all the settings you\'d need, including a delayed timer and a choice between brew strengths, but my favorite feature has to be that most of this machine can be taken apart for cleaning. We have hard water, so minerals build up quickly in the water tanks of our coffee makers. We\'ve always struggled to clean them, having to run vinegar through a couple cycles to get everything cleared out. With this model, however, the tank comes right off for cleaning!'),
(6954, 6, 1, 5, '2016-09-08', 'Five Stars Great toaster.'),
(6955, 6, 1, 2, '2014-10-08', 'Problems after 2 1/2 months I have had this toaster since July ( it is now Oct 8) and I am having problems with the heating elements and regulating the color of the toast.  When I first received it, the toaster worked fine, but then for no reason (because the toaster has not been abused) I am having all these issues.  I expected more form Cuisinart.  Not happy at all with this toaster.'),
(6956, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-25', 'Five Stars Use it every day.'),
(6957, 9, 1, 2, '2015-11-18', 'Noisy brewing process. Makes good coffee, nice and hot. However, the loud noise during brewing is unbearable. Listened to that \"gurgling\" while brewing only 8 cups. Imagine what it will be like to brew 12 cups. The first one I purchased was returned for that reason. The replacement appears to be even louder. I suppose that if one sets up the auto brew early enough by the time one gets up the ordeal is over. I can\'t stand it and that\'s why it\'s being returned for credit.'),
(6958, 6, 1, 2, '2015-06-27', 'unacceptable I bought this a year and a half ago from a competitor because I wanted black.  It\'s primary quality is that it\'s the smallest decent-looking entirely insulated toaster available.  But some cheaper ones toast better.  Like many others I\'ve found that it toasts vastly more on the inside than on the outside, which over time appears to be getting worse.  It has a bagel setting that\'s supposed to do exactly that, and I would guess that the fault lies with it.  But it has a related quirk in that it toasts two slices less brown on the same setting than one, placed in either slot.  In other words, if you do one slice you have to turn the temp dial down a half point to get the same result as when you do two, and vice versa, up a half for two, from one.  The cancel button and reheat buttons do no more than just adjusting the color and pulling on the handle of any old toaster.  The slots are wide enough for most bagels and long enough for most wide-pan bread.  The crumb tray is novel in that it slides out, but it slides out from the back.  I would think if we can get to the moon, we can make a toaster, but nobody seems to be able to make a waffle iron as well as they did 50 years ago either.'),
(6959, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Five Stars toasts bread....'),
(6960, 2, 1, 5, '2016-10-14', 'I\'m not a good cook. I have never been I\'m not a good cook. I have never been, and I never will be. Since I have to cook, I look for simple and easy ways to cook things. This was my solution. If you don\'t need something elaborate or fancy and you don\'t intend to cook gourmet foods, this is perfect. I make salmon, toast, bagels, etc in this daily. It\'s inexpensive and it does what it needs to do, for a good price. I needed simple and efficient, and this cooks my food and was a good price so I got what I paid for and I\'m satisfied. I\'ve had no issues, it\'s easy to use, so I\'d recommend it.'),
(6961, 7, 3, 5, '2014-01-14', 'Convenient and easy to use. Great value. Plan to buy a second one for the office'),
(6962, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-21', 'Five Stars Perfect size~'),
(6963, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Loving my Keurig K250 This is my second experience with a Keurig 2.0 and I\'m loving the purchase. I have a K500 at home and I recently purchased the K250 in turquoise for my office at work. I love this product because I still have the option of brewing a carafe without the brewer having to be so big. I would recommend a Keurig to anyone who loves coffee, it brews a great cup all the time! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(6964, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-06', 'Love the chrome color as well as size fits nicely ... Love the chrome color as well as size fits nicely on my counter top easy to clean highly recommend this product'),
(6965, 5, 1, 3, '2015-05-18', 'Three Stars Died a few months ago...'),
(6966, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-19', 'Four Stars Nice and lightweight with good settings.  One piece of toast does not toast evenly on both sides.'),
(6967, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-03', 'Works surprisingly well and great price! Has worked well. Not a ninja but for the cost and the longevity, I had to give it 5 stars. I use it daily.'),
(6968, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-27', 'I Highly Anticipate a Recall First of all I have been using Black and Decker toaster ovens since college (about 20 years). I have never had an issue before now. This oven emits a very strong burning smell, as in wires burning. This cooks way too quickly. The heating coil is actually too powerful. Example: I heated a frozen mini baguette which the package says to preheat oven to 400 degrees. I preheated this toaster oven to 250 degrees and still the outside of the bread was beginning to burn after 5 minutes. There was also smoke coming out of the top. Whatever you are cooking you CANNOT let this toaster oven out of your sight. Your food WILL burn and it may even catch fire. Also when opening the toaster oven door be very careful because the handle will be hot. This does seem like a major fire hazard. I also think this is a quality control failure on the part of Black and Decker, which is a risk to the brand.'),
(6969, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-01', 'I love this coffee maker I love this coffee maker! I have a french press but this is my go to machine on work mornings. It is very easy to operate and I love waking up to already brewed coffee.'),
(6970, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-01', 'Thoughtful Design I especially like the removable water reservoir as well as the fact that it\'s difficult to spill water while using this carafe (super valuable for a klutz like me). I was reluctant to buy this, since we already have a functioning 4-cup coffee machine, but the hubby wanted the option of brewing 12 cups in one go. After using this for 1 month, I have to say that I\'m definitely pleased with it. My only wish is for this exact coffeemaker to be available in half its size. :)'),
(6971, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-06', 'Does the job Bought it for individual protein shakes. Chops the frozen fruit and the nuts and does a good job of mixing the ingredients.'),
(6972, 10, 1, 5, '2015-08-05', 'Great For $15, this is a killer deal. Ignore the burning rubber smell; it works best if you do vegetables, raw fruit, yogurt, or other softer things on the bottom and frozen fruit on the top.'),
(6973, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-22', 'Fresh and convenient I have had the pleasure of using this machine for about 6 weeks now at my work place.  The convenience and freshness of each cup are well worth the price!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(6974, 7, 3, 2, '2015-12-25', 'On my first few attempts to brew a cup of coffee using the K-cups feature all the water ended up on the counter and maybe 2 ounces in the mug. I finally figured out if i peeled the entire lid off the K-cup this was the only way I could successfully brew a cup of coffee but I still had the water everywhere. You get whet you pay for but if you do not want the headache and agony most of us (read the rest of the reviews) go through pay a little more for a better machine. I will be returning mine to do the same. This problem is specify with the K-cups feature, works fine brewing ground coffee. There seems to be a drippage failure with my machine since I have to remove the entire lid of the K-cup for water to flow through. Do yourselves a favor and do some research before buying this machine.'),
(6975, 4, 1, 3, '2015-03-10', 'Be careful! We love what this toaster oven can do, but sometimes, it smokes when it shouldn\'t. Don\'t leave anything on top of it while you\'re using it! Also, I now unplug it the moment it\'s done toasting something.'),
(6976, 9, 1, 2, '2016-05-31', 'It is less than a year old but it drips coffee like a leaky faucet The dispenser valve on this machine is defective. It is less than a year old but it drips coffee like a leaky faucet.It fills the catch tray and runs all over the counter - big mess. A relative in Torontoi had the same coffee pot and it also leaked coffee. They need to fix this at the factory.'),
(6977, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-29', 'A good coffee maker, a decent price! A nice coffee pot...I like the fact that the base has a roller on it so I can pull it out from under my cabinets and most of all I like the removable water resevoir...it makes cleaning a breeze!'),
(6978, 2, 1, 1, '2015-01-24', 'Arrived and doesn\'t even work. The light indicates that ... Arrived and doesn\'t even work. The light indicates that it\'s plugged in and turned on, but neither of the heating rods light up and it doesn\'t cook...'),
(6979, 6, 1, 2, '2014-09-19', 'One-Sided Toasting and inoperable after 15 months to boot! I bought this model about 15 months ago.  Not only does it not toast both sides of the bread, but today it simply stopped working-the lever would not engage and there was no heat whatsoever. There is this model at my work, and it has lasted several years, though it doesn\'t toast both sides either. It\'s a laugh to call it a \"toaster\"!'),
(6980, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-07', 'very good Works as expected, very good quality'),
(6981, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-31', 'A1 coffee maker Outstanding unit, we are very happy with the DCC-3000  it makes a great hot cup.'),
(6982, 12, 1, 4, '2014-11-18', 'Four Stars It works. After some time and heavy usage it gets beaten but never stops.'),
(6983, 5, 1, 1, '2015-10-01', 'Crap Died within a month of use. I drink 1-2 pots of coffee a day. Know it doesn\'t need to be cleaned because it doesn\'t even making the brewing sound. Better off buying a $15 coffee maker.'),
(6984, 8, 1, 5, '2014-08-31', 'Five Stars Excellent!!!'),
(6985, 4, 1, 1, '2015-09-27', 'After two years of use, lower heating element failed. I received this toaster oven as a Christmas gift and it worked well for a year and a half.  I used it daily for toast.  Six months ago I noticed the lower front heating element was starting to crack and glow.  I have replaced many Cal-rod type heaters over the years so I thought, no big deal.  I will but replacements and change them out.  NOT GONNA HAPPEN.  Cuisinart does not sell replacements. The front element arced out this morning so I can no longer toast my bread.  I will not get another Cuisinart product as they are clearly, based on other one star reviews, quite content to sell a product that is guaranteed to fail past the warrentee period.  Not even offering replacement parts for a well known failure mode is not acceptable. Gonna look at Panasonic infrared units....'),
(6986, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-18', 'confusing controls, died within a month Bought this from a department store where I had a gift card after reading the positive reviews. What confusing controls! Had to set 3 dials just to toast. And even once you\'ve got that set up, you have to do this weird thing where you crank the bottom dial past a marker then rotate it backwards to the setting you want. Ok...well I hated that but figured I could live with it since it liked that it toasted fast. (Last toaster took absolutely forever.) But it just died today...it doesn\'t heat up anymore. After only a month. This is my third toaster in as many years...not sure why it is so hard to find a decent toaster oven, it\'s a simple enough appliance! Edited to add: ok just went back to the mall and visited several stores. not only is this toaster everywhere, I\'m perplexed tthat almost EVERY brand has the same sort of dials. They all say something like \"turn to 20, then to desired time. \" ?? Why? ugh. Finally found a sunbeam at sears that has simpler dials and was under twenty.'),
(6987, 10, 1, 2, '2015-03-03', 'so so I purchased this item for my son he said is OK but it really doesn\'t blend that well you have to slice up a banana in order for it to blend the motor is not that strong.'),
(6988, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-31', 'Great oven Great oven for a small household like ours. I use it practically every day for baking.'),
(6989, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-10', 'LOVE IT! I\'ve had this toaster oven years ago LOVE IT!  I\'ve had this toaster oven years ago, so when I moved, I HAD to repurchase the same exact model.  It\'s durable and has great settings that actually work!  I can even bake a 10\"-12\" pizza in there perfectly.'),
(6990, 7, 3, 5, '2014-12-31', 'Awesome product. No longer will be controlled by the expensive price of keurig. Very affordable better because you can use regular coffee grinds also. I recommend it to everyone!'),
(6991, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-12', 'Great Toaster Ignome negative reviews. This is a great Toaster that works perfectly. It is compact and easy to use. You need to do a few \"trials\" to get the exact toast  you want but once you find your desired  degree of \"doneness\" you are good to go. I have had many toasters over the years and this is by far the best. This has a gracious array of features and an excellent value for price.'),
(6992, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-04', 'Five Stars great toaster'),
(6993, 12, 1, 1, '2015-04-11', 'Flimsy construction. Likely to break after a few uses. Flimsy. Poor quality. Feels like it will break after only a few uses. Don\'t buy or return immediately.'),
(6994, 6, 1, 5, '2015-09-04', 'Happy with it Easy to use. Nice toaster.'),
(6995, 2, 1, 1, '2016-04-26', 'One Star This broke and I only have had it a couple of months'),
(6996, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-28', 'Keurig is great! Quick, easy to use and there are so many great tasting coffees! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(6997, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-19', 'Great Toaster!! I don\'t know how I ever lived without this toaster. It\'s nice looking, digital, easy to use and I love that it remembers my last setting. I would recommend this product to my family.'),
(6998, 8, 1, 5, '2014-09-29', 'Five Stars Great deal!  Fast delivery.'),
(6999, 9, 1, 1, '2017-01-17', 'It worked well for awhile but then flooded my counter ... It worked well for awhile but then flooded my counter twice, dripping on the floor after I filled my cup.  The lever that you push to fill your cup never worked well after and continued leaking.  This was my second Cuisinart - the first one literally started on fire in my kitchen out of the blue and now this one flooded my counter and dripped in between my cabinets.  So done with this company.'),
(7000, 2, 1, 4, '2015-04-06', 'Very good toaster compared to others we have tried in this ... Very good toaster compared to others we have tried in this one`s price range. Good even heat. \"Light\" toast setting range could be broader - it\'s a little difficult to get the same setting every time, other than that, it\'s Great'),
(7001, 3, 1, 4, '2015-01-20', 'Good Value I love this toaster oven.  It\'s a great size, heats very quickly and easy to use.  Please NOTE, however, that the door falls to the counter when you open it.  There are no hinges to slow it.  Be careful not to drop the door open.  Also, there is no internal courtesy light.'),
(7002, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-15', 'Five Stars Awesome Appliance, at a very reasonable price.'),
(7003, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-08', 'Five Stars Really like.'),
(7004, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-26', 'Works great! I use it to make my protein shakes ... Works great!  I use it to make my protein shakes and to grind coffee beans!  Very easy to clean.'),
(7005, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-24', 'we love this coffee pot we love this coffee pot. We have tried the other carafe free pots and they do not compare to this one. A little more expensive but well worth the extra money. very solidly built and well thought design.'),
(7006, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-17', 'Four Stars as expected'),
(7007, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-23', 'Solid pot for a good price. I love coffee, and drink maybe a pot a day.  I had a really nice coffee maker with a built in grinder, when it packed it in after 3 years I went looking for a traditional drip coffee maker because I didn\'t lose both my grinder and coffee maker again when only one went south. This isn\'t the most expensive unit, but I have to say I would not hesitate to buy it again.  I like how I can remove the water reservoir, the clock keeps the right time (an actual issue on my old pot), and it is easy to program.  Most importantly, it makes good coffee once you figure out the right ratios.'),
(7008, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-29', 'heated up to a high temperature at any setting. ... heated up to a high temperature at any setting. I kept trying to adjust. By the time I realized it was a faulty product, I could no longer send it back!!!   Very, very, displeased.'),
(7009, 4, 1, 5, '2016-08-22', 'Excellent Functionality and Quality Works great, and I enjoy the extracting tray. The tray makes it convenient to remove toasted items from the oven easily and safely, and helps ensure you don\'t burn your fingers when removing something from the rack. Excellent functionality and quality materials and workmanship. I would highly recommend this product over the many other name brand toaster ovens I have previously owned.'),
(7010, 7, 3, 1, '2017-01-02', 'Bought this for my mother to replace one that broke. Waste of time and money. She used it ONCE and it broke just like the other one.'),
(7011, 10, 1, 4, '2016-03-27', 'Four Stars Does as advertised..'),
(7012, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-01', 'Five Stars Best coffee maker I ever had, this is #2 in 4 years. Great product.'),
(7013, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Great  single serve brewer Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review. We had the Keurig mini for our motorhome which we loved but the 250 has a better water reservoir and it came with lots of assorted extras including coffee and tea pods. Everyone loves the taste of the coffee from the Keurig pods.'),
(7014, 8, 1, 4, '2015-03-28', 'Works fine Came as described and on time, works fine.'),
(7015, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-18', 'Five Stars very nice and works wonderful'),
(7016, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-13', 'Nice choice on a budget We like this toaster.  Looks nice, toasts the bread etc.  We had a big fancy expensive Cuisinart before this one, but needed to spend less this time around. Only real complaint so far is that the tray gets stained.  I toast my bread with oil-packed sundried tomatoes and cheese, and the oil seeps through the bread and gets baked onto the tray in a non-removable way.  This never happened with previous toaster oven trays that had more of an enamel finish.  This tray seems low quality.'),
(7017, 12, 1, 3, '2015-01-04', 'Three Stars Theres no button for the oven part, so be careful kids dont mess with the buttons.'),
(7018, 4, 1, 2, '2016-11-09', 'This oven was really \"cheesy\" - quality was poor and it has no design improvements since my last ... I returned this item.  Cuisinart has not lived up to my expectations as a Cuisinart customer.  This oven was really \"cheesy\" - quality was poor and it has no design improvements since my last one about 10 years ago.  I bought a Hamilton Beach with somewhat better quality and MUCH lower price.'),
(7019, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-15', 'Love it. So easy to use I bought this to have for quick post workout shakes rather than using the ninja. Love it. So easy to use. It isn\'t a heavy duty processor but works great with frozen berries protein water and or ice. easy to clean too.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(7020, 8, 1, 3, '2015-12-17', 'Bad design makes for sub-par coffee and died after 9 months Pros: Makes coffee. 5 Cups is a good size. Cons: Poor quality-only lasted about 9 months of daily use. Bad basket design harms coffee flavor. No sneak-a-cup feature. Immediately upon using this coffee maker I was unhappy with the coffee it brewed. It was too weak. A quick peek inside the basket showed me why: the ridges in the bottom of the basket are too small, forcing all the water to funnel toward the middle, digging a little hole as it flows and skipping most of the coffee grounds. I worked around this by placing an extra coffee filter on *top* of the grounds. (I know, wasteful, but it worked.) Also, there\'s no sneak-a-cup feature, so when the coffee is finished brewing you still need to wait a couple of minutes to serve yourself because the basket will keep dripping for a while. I was constantly dripping coffee onto the warming plate. I disliked this model so much that I finally just ordered a new Mr. Coffee in black from Amazon and dawdled a few weeks about switching it out until the Black and Decker made it easy for me by dying after about 9 months of use. To be fair, I probably brew 3 to 4 pots of coffee a day, but I\'d been doing that with my old Mr. Coffee for about a decade and it was still going strong. TL/DR: Skip this, buy a Mr. Coffee Edit: Changed rating from 2 to 3 stars because of fast contact from customer service.'),
(7021, 8, 1, 4, '2016-02-15', '$13 coffee pot.  No surprises. It brews coffee, takes longer than I can wait.  I scream and cry for the coffee to brew faster, but I think wait I paid $13 for this, what did I expect.'),
(7022, 5, 1, 3, '2015-06-26', 'coffee maker easy to sue however the colon on the clock continually ... coffee maker easy to sue however the colon on the clock continually blinks and the time can accidentally be changed if you hit the hour or minute button by mistake...no way to lock the time and it does not automatically lock after programing....am returning it, customer service told me that is just the way it is'),
(7023, 2, 1, 5, '2016-08-14', 'Five Stars Great toaster for a very affordable price.'),
(7024, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-18', 'Five Stars Excellent item!'),
(7025, 5, 1, 3, '2015-01-25', 'lukewarm and bitter, burnt brew The coffee temperature is not hot enough and the flavor of the coffee is not good. We put each cup of freshly brewed coffee in the microwave. We tried the recommendation, use hot water for brewing but it\'s still not up to our standard.'),
(7026, 3, 1, 4, '2016-02-11', 'It is awesome for frozen snacks and entrees but it does not ... I would have given this product 5 stars but it came with a nonstick interior which the information given does not specify! For this problem alone i was going to send it back. It also does not come with a recipe book. The oven itself is very light but it performs all functions very well. It is awesome for frozen snacks and entrees but it does not beep very loud. I have a great little timer so that does not bother me.  Overall a great little oven!'),
(7027, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-16', 'I love it, very neat on my counter top I love it, very neat on my counter top. very satisfied with the performance. I highly recommended this Toaster Oven to anyone that just need  a neat space occupied on their counter top.'),
(7028, 8, 1, 4, '2016-10-02', 'Simple and Functional Awesome value for money. Basic in functionality but does everything it promises and easy to use.'),
(7029, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'I love my Keurig coffee maker I love my Keurig coffee maker.  I really enjoy drinking a fresh cup of coffee every time.  I even bought a mini to use for travel. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(7030, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-02', 'Five Stars Perfect size for our boat. We use it every weekend when we sleep on the boat.'),
(7031, 11, 1, 2, '2014-08-26', 'The control for toast does not work correctly. Setting ... The control for toast does not work correctly.  Setting the degree of \"doneness\" even at a very low level produces burnt toast.  It\'s really a \"manual\" toaster\"!'),
(7032, 7, 3, 3, '2016-03-16', 'I pot this for my mom to be able to change up the normal return of instant coffee. this is the first k cup coffee maker we\'ve ever had. its very simple and easy to use. unfortunately only 3 months later it stopped working. I purchased the extra care plan just in case since it was so cheap. I went to file a claim to get it fixed or exchanged. I will be trading for a new one. until it arrives she is back to instant coffee .'),
(7033, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-17', 'Good so far I like this unit - well built, attractive, does a good job on toasting, and easy to keep clean. Like the controls, easy to dial in and not to busy. The removable tray for cleaning crumbs covers the entire bottom and slides right out without opening the door. Temperatures seem to be good - I have not done lots of baking/broiling - but what i have done seems good. The toasting for light/dark dial seems consistent. The only thing I thought was not user friendly is being able to easily seem where the index point for the 3 knobs is located. The knobs have a nice black plastic insert with ridges which are easy to accurately adjust. The problem is the index on each knob is one of the ridges in the black area is raised higher than the others. I just took a white paint pen and drew a line on the raised ridge - very easy to see. Others complained the lettering for the dials is too small - I wear glasses and can see it OK without glasses.'),
(7034, 2, 1, 2, '2015-08-30', 'Toaster Have had problems making toast, as I use thin sliced. It has been burned on me a couple of times. My old black and Decker( circa 1990)never had a problem. The noise this unit makes is more agin to a cheap wind up kitchen timer, and no where as exact.  Also the insulatin is not as good as my old one, this one the sides get hoy'),
(7035, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-03', 'Family Knows My sister told me about this, her advice happened to be the best.'),
(7036, 2, 1, 2, '2016-10-18', 'very small interior, doesn\'t handle 8\" square pans. Interior dimensions must be at the very bottom most spot. The door is angled back so far I can\'t even fit an 8\" square pan into the toaster oven. I\'m sure it works well enough for what it is, but it doesn\'t have the capacity to hold what I need it to hold.'),
(7037, 11, 1, 3, '2014-07-24', 'Three Stars I liked my old model black & decker much better'),
(7038, 5, 1, 4, '2014-05-21', 'Hamilton Beach Coffeemaker Finally got to use this...easy to use, but wish it were a smaller unit. I am sure the coffee will taste better each time I prepare; was disappointed with the first cups, but probably didn\'t use the amount of grounds that it really requires, obviously more needed than my Mr. Coffee.'),
(7039, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-14', 'Exactly what I was looking for! I have been very please with this coffee maker.  I had a Cuisinart the last purchase but I did not want to spend that much this time around because the amount of deposits that I have in my water.  I was looking for something more cost effective but just as nice.  This fit the bill.  I bought the permanent gold tone filter to use with it and I have been very happy!'),
(7040, 12, 1, 5, '2014-08-12', 'Five Stars Really enjoy this item'),
(7041, 5, 1, 5, '2016-11-05', 'Five Stars Very good.'),
(7042, 5, 1, 3, '2015-06-10', 'beautiful machine ....but a calcium trap We have owned this coffee maker for a little over a year. It\'s a beautiful piece of equipment for sure BUT there is an issue that needs to be addressed . Hopefully this will at least help the people that have already purchased this , as well a possible buyers. We had to run vinegar and CLR through this machine more than any machine we ever owned. Which is unfortunate since it really was great up until now .easily one of the nicest ones we have owned up until this point. Finally last week it completely stopped flowing. I took the entire thing apart and looked it over well before I tossed it. Some piece of mind for me and you. What I found was a complete , rock solid calcium clog in the -U- shaped heating chamber which is located right on the bottom of the unit when you take the cover off (the bottom). There are 2 orange hoses that Connect to it. The side that seems to clog is the one with the heating element attached to it. You may be able to unclog it with a coat hanger if things get really bad. Hope this helps someone. Thanks for your time .'),
(7043, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-08', 'Great for small kitchens!! It really does both.  I have very little counter space and with this I just need one appliance.  Easy to use and prefect for one or two people.'),
(7044, 11, 1, 3, '2014-02-14', 'Does the job Not the best toast maker, but I got it to warm up small item I do not want use my large oven for so it serves that purpose well.  I much prefer the older B&D toast ovens.'),
(7045, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-08', 'A winner It\'s our 2nd one and hopefully will give us the same great cup of coffee as the first'),
(7046, 7, 3, 5, '2015-12-11', 'I never had a coffee maker that used K pods or paks, and friends would go to the store for me and bring me pods, so I had to break them open to use the ground coffee. I saw this Hamilton Beach coffeemaker and thought it was the best idea ever! When my coffee maker died, I bought this one and splurged on the red one. I\'m SO glad I did. It makes the best ground coffee and I now can use pods! It was easy to fit together and I have coffee in minutes!'),
(7047, 2, 1, 2, '2015-08-03', 'Solid toaster, great price, but too sensitive and awful knobs. Fantastic price. It toasts quickly and evenly. Hot glue smell to start, but it went away after a couple long test toasts the first day. Now it\'s going to get pretty pedantic: I really hate the knobs. It\'s the only toaster I\'ve ever used in my life that has big round knobs instead of the pinch-and-turn type knobs (like you\'d find on every stove everywhere). I know it sounds insanely nitpicky, bit with the pinch-type knob it\'s markedly easier to \"feel\" how much you\'ve turned one without looking closely. With my old toaster, a 45-turn was usually the right setting, easy to pull off instantly, and there was some leeway. With this toaster it\'s more like half that, and an errant extra ten degrees in your turn could burn your bread. I\'m going to see if I can pull off the timer knob and replace it with a pinch-type, because I hate grabbing a big dumb knob and peering closely at it like I\'m trying to bring in a fireside chat. If you definitely won\'t be bothered by the knob, it\'s a really good model. But it gets two stars from me because I hate the part of it I have to touch every time.'),
(7048, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-01', 'Convenience and space saver I loved this product so much when my first one wore out, I immediately ordered another.'),
(7049, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-18', 'Easy to clean though Controls are awkward, cant just push a button and toast.  Cannot walk away from this little oven while cooking, likes to burn toast.  Have used 20 plus times and still dont have it dialed in to make garlic cheese toast.  Wouldnt buy again.  Gets very hot on top, thin and cheap but what do you expect at this price point. Easy to clean though.'),
(7050, 9, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Five Stars Great throughout.'),
(7051, 9, 1, 4, '2015-04-24', 'Four Stars coffee ready for you in the morning'),
(7052, 1, 1, 5, '2016-09-06', 'Love it!! Love the bright color!!.'),
(7053, 4, 1, 1, '2015-08-06', 'Bottom element cracked open and burnt We purchased this toaster oven in 2012 based on the popularity on Amazon. We are a small family and do not use the regular oven much. so this one was a great alternative for us when we needed to toast some bread or just heat up a trader joes frozen pizza for one person. It was fast and convenient. But, recently I noticed there was some sort of light inside of the oven that I didn\'t recall it had one before. Today I finally came to realize that the \'light\' at the bottom right was an opening of the cracked element! It was bended and burnt. We didn\'t expect it to be such a short lived one since we didn\'t even use it everyday. What a bummer! I\'m writing this review to let the potential buyers know about it since I read so many other users experienced the same problem. Those negative reviews were not there when I purchased it in 2012.'),
(7054, 4, 1, 2, '2016-10-20', 'Two Stars NO GOOD.'),
(7055, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-13', 'I really like this blender I really like this blender. I have made so many different types of smoothies over the last few days. When I first got the blender and used it, the blender had a burning smell. I think the smell has gone away. Note: please make sure not to pack this blender it is a good blender but by no means this not a Ninja Blender.'),
(7056, 7, 3, 4, '2014-09-12', 'Good low cost K-cup coffee maker'),
(7057, 5, 1, 3, '2016-10-21', 'Three Stars Sometimes doesn\'t work well.'),
(7058, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-20', 'Five Stars Great!'),
(7059, 2, 1, 2, '2015-12-03', 'Difficult to use I\'ve always had black and decker toaster ovens, they work well. However with this version the design team was out to lunch. The control labels are barely legible and impossible to decipher.'),
(7060, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Thank you Keurig for the FREE PODS for this review! We have our coffee maker (Keurig K250 2.0 brew system) about 3 weeks now and we love it.  We had to replace our old one because the motor went.  Our older model Keurig\'s never brewed a carafe size pot.  We love that feature when we have company.  The only thing missing is a programmable timer.  Other than that we love how it brews, and we have been hooked on Keurig for approximately 5 years now. Thank you to Keurig Company, for the free pods, for this review.'),
(7061, 8, 1, 2, '2015-10-22', 'Water Leaks from bottom. I bought this in store, but just wanted to warn people that only after 6 brew cycles, I am seeing water leaking from the bottom. I do not over fill as I only brew 3 cups at a time. Not sure what I can do to return it......not even sure where the water is coming from. I do like the brewer itself as its small enough for my desk at work, but not worth all the water leaking after each use now... not worth your money.'),
(7062, 3, 1, 5, '2016-01-09', 'Five Stars Gave as a gift and they loved it.'),
(7063, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-31', 'good buy looks good, works great, easy to use.'),
(7064, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-20', 'for the price, perfect! I\'ve used this thing a total of 5 times now (once a day), and for one purpose only (protein shake) the ingredients of which are: milk, protein powder, ice, 2-3 inches of raw banana (not too ripe, so not super soft). For $17, and for my purpose, i can\'t imagine a better value. The only con i can think of is that  while the machine is blending, i can smell that mechanical motor scent. not sure if you know what i mean by that, but it\'s the same smell i get sometimes when using my kitchenaid hand mixer... It\'s not impacting my protein shake, obviously... The product is otherwise flawless. Just hope it lasts.'),
(7065, 2, 1, 3, '2016-02-18', 'Works great but we\'re not crazy about the timer/switch We bought the b & d toaster almost exclusively to toast.  Works great but we\'re not crazy about the timer/switch.  You have to keep an eye on the toasting progress or your bread will burn; a medium level inconvenience.'),
(7066, 8, 1, 4, '2016-08-18', 'Four Stars does the job!.'),
(7067, 6, 1, 5, '2016-10-14', 'Five Stars awesome.'),
(7068, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-06', 'Five Stars so far so good, working well.'),
(7069, 6, 1, 4, '2015-10-02', 'workes great workes great'),
(7070, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-20', 'Five Stars Perfect.'),
(7071, 9, 1, 5, '2015-03-04', 'I LOVE IT! I LOVE IT!!!! works great, makes great coffee, holds a lot of coffee in the back. I couldn\'t be happier.'),
(7072, 3, 1, 3, '2016-04-08', 'Three Stars Top part should be made from better material (not thin aluminum) , cracking noise every time you toast.'),
(7073, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-29', 'Great small oven toaster Just love it for the price and the function. Received on time'),
(7074, 2, 1, 4, '2015-04-13', 'smaller than expected Ok except was smaller than my last one.  Would have paid more for one a little bigger had I known'),
(7075, 5, 1, 4, '2015-05-12', 'I really like being able to take the water container off to ... Read all the reviews I could before deciding on this purchase.  I really like being able to take the water container off to fill the machine.  Easy and no mess.  Vast improvement over the old black and decker I had been using.  Even when pouring coffee, it is pretty much spill proof.  The only draw back is that it is a little noisy at times Overall, I am well satisfied.'),
(7076, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-12', 'Five Stars Great product!!! Very satisfied...'),
(7077, 11, 1, 4, '2015-06-23', 'Great toaster with lots of settings that aren\'t overwhelming Great toaster with lots of settings that aren\'t overwhelming. My only wish is that the \"ding!\" at the end of toasting was louder or went off more consistently. I always seem to miss it.'),
(7078, 9, 1, 2, '2015-09-09', 'Does not make a good pot of coffee I will be buying another brand/style soon.  I love the on-demand style of coffee maker over a carafe, but this one is too finicky.  Slightly too many grounds and it jams up and the coffee stream won\'t turn off.  Floods the counter and floor. Therefore there is little adjustment available for stronger coffee. Coffee tends to be muddy.'),
(7079, 2, 1, 4, '2015-05-04', 'if you want toast it is better to use a toaster It works okay.  Used it initially for a science project my son was doing.  It was the incubator.  Now I just use it in the kitchen and as a previous reviewer said, if you want toast it is better to use a toaster.'),
(7080, 5, 1, 1, '2016-10-22', 'Just awful... Do not buy this. You will be buying another coffee maker in just a few months. The first one amazon sent broke immediately before we even brewed coffee in it. We opened the swinging door to put in some coffee grounds and the faceplate fell right off. The screws that were used to secure it had broken the cheap plastic at both contact points. So we sent it back and Amazon replaced it. The second one was good for about a month or two. This time however, it was the carafe that was the problem. After brewing a pot in the morning, we noticed coffee all over the counter. We lifted the carafe out and coffee started pouring out the bottom. The bottom of it had just crumbled... Honestly, you\'re better off with a $20 Mr. Coffee.'),
(7081, 11, 1, 2, '2014-04-11', 'Stopped working within a month.  The heating element died and I am without a toaster. The toaster oven stopped working after only a month or six weeks.  When I tried to toast bread this morning the element was dead.'),
(7082, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-05', 'Excellent toaster Nice even browning of any kind of toast. Very happy with this toaster.'),
(7083, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-12', 'For most uses, great product I think overall this is a good product, but it does have some significant drawbacks that could make it unhelpful for some uses. This is our second Keurig. We previously had an older non 2.0 model. I like the clean overall look of the machine and think it fits well on our counter. I like that they moved the water tank to the back of the machine although I wish it would hold as much as our other Keurig did. If you do not want to use the Keurig approved K-cups then this would not be the machine for you unless you learn how to hack it. For my husband, the coffee drinker, this machine works great. I on the other hand am a tea drinker and the tea I prefer is not yet available in a K-cup so I buy the tea bags and just brew hot water. The 250 will only let me brew 4 to 6 oz. at a time. To \"unlock\" the bigger sizes, you must have a K-cup in the holder. Therefore, to get an 8 oz. cup of tea I have to brew two 4 oz. cycles of hot water. While in the grand scheme of things it does not take that much extra time to simply run the process twice, I do not understand why the standard oz. sizes are not available no matter what you are brewing, like the older machine we own did. We have not yet used the carafe feature and are unlikely too since we usually just have one cup each of our preferred beverage in the morning. Overall, I think this is a good product but Keurig still has some work to do before I will give them 5 stars. I received this product for free to use and review.'),
(7084, 1, 1, 5, '2015-07-01', 'Great colors I love this Keurig, I have had other Keurig brewers in the past and had a good experience, what led me to purchase this one was that I loved the color... I love that it can brew the carafe size pods, down side is that you have to make sure you buy the new Keurig k-cups... I had to give away some of the older style ones because they could not be read. The coffee is good and hot, I love the different sizes, one more feature I would\'ve like to have seen would have been an auto-off feature as my last one had that. Over all, I am very pleased. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review'),
(7085, 4, 1, 5, '2016-05-03', 'I\'m glad I bought this Yeah. I\'m glad I bought this. I just wish I had a good place to keep the tray when not in use. Gotta reorganize my cabinets.'),
(7086, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-25', 'I got this a bit over a month ago and ... I got this a bit over a month ago and have used it daily for smoothies with frozen fruit/almond milk and a handful of times for mixed drinks with ice. No issues with it so far. Just ordered a second one so I can make smoothies at work also without having bring the part that plugs into the wall in too. I read that some people had problems with the lid after using the dish washer but I haven\'t I\'ve only put it through the dish washer about 5 times but no issue yet. Its mostly been run through by accident because my girlfriend forgets that it shouldn\'t be. Since I am going to have two of them I might just start dish washing them until I run into a problem though.'),
(7087, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-21', 'Five Stars PERFECT'),
(7088, 6, 1, 5, '2014-07-27', 'Great Toaster Great Toaster. It is light weight and not too big. The controls work well. You can make super light to super dark toast and bagels and it works great on frozen waffles and frozen pastries. You can have light toast on one side and dark toast on the other side or the same toast setting on both sides. It reheats without toasting and it has a defrost setting too. I really love having a 4 slice toaster too.'),
(7089, 10, 1, 4, '2015-06-09', 'Pretty good The good is that it is portable and easily cleanable. The bad is that the blade isn\'t the best. It mixes fine and chops things up okay. Overall it\'s a cheap blender that\'s easy to use and I would recommend it.'),
(7090, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-20', 'Five Stars I just love this Brand and the toast is toasted on both sides.'),
(7091, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-03', 'Five Stars Very good product and fast delivery!'),
(7092, 8, 1, 1, '2015-12-05', 'Don\'t waste your money Stopped working after about 3 months. Don\'t waste your money.'),
(7093, 5, 1, 1, '2016-07-17', 'The case of the disappearing water Less than nine months after purchasing this pot, it is going in the garbage.  From day one I noticed how cheaply made it is... the face plate pops off every time I push the button to open the door to the basket, so I just developed the habit of holding the plate on while opening the door.  But this week it started doing something that I cannot explain.  I (try to) make a pot of coffee as usual, but only half a pot of coffee comes out, and the rest of the water just disappears.  There is no water left in the reservoir, no water in the grounds basket, no water on the countertop, and only half a pot of coffee in the carafe.  This happened three times in a row, and I have no clue where the water is going... but it isn\'t making coffee.'),
(7094, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-10', 'Five Stars Makes coffee just as advertised. To complaints or criticisms yet.'),
(7095, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-10', 'It does beautiful simple smoothies and protein shakes I\'ve owned one of these since 2008! It does beautiful simple smoothies and protein shakes.  Go easy on the icey stuff thou, this in NOT a full sized blender so it can be hard on the motor.  I microwave on defrost for a few seconds(like 20) any big hard frozen fruit, like peaches and strawberries.. That way they are still cold and it\'s easier on the blender. Great little hand blender for quick breakfasts in the morning!'),
(7096, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', 'Five Stars Does the job perfectly in the morning!'),
(7097, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'Great toaster! Purchased this months ago, still going strong.  Great toaster!'),
(7098, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'I love my keurig 2 I love my keurig 2.0. It goes above and beyond to get my morning started right with the best cup of coffee around. Easy and user friendly. Be sure to always descale your keurig. Thank you keurig for my 2 free boxes of pods for this review.'),
(7099, 10, 1, 2, '2015-02-26', 'Cheap and it shows. While very inexpensive, the blender cup has failed on three consecutive units. The seal around the shaft just doesn\'t last. Beware of short lifespan.'),
(7100, 10, 1, 4, '2015-10-23', 'Four Stars Great for traveling with.'),
(7101, 10, 1, 1, '2016-02-20', 'burns up easily. Okay if you like shakes that taste like ... Junk. Motor underpowered, burns up easily. Okay if you like shakes that taste like electrical insulation. Threw it out.'),
(7102, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-23', 'Fantastic Design This is a really well designed coffee maker. It\'s simple to use and has a bunch of easy to use features and I really like the removable water container instead of the usual way where you fill up the coffee pot with water then pour it into the abyss. Even the coffee pot itself feels nice when holding. I first bought the Mr. Coffee BVMC-SJX33GT but returned it when all the grinds were getting into the pot. This one is much better.'),
(7103, 6, 1, 5, '2014-02-04', 'Easy to use.  toasts great. I have used this now for about a week.  It toasts english muffins and bagels just right.  I really like the clear easy to see buttons and dial.  It also has a nice feature where when your done cooking you reverse the slider up and you can get your stuff out without worrying about getting a shock. That is something I have never had in a toaster and I like it.'),
(7104, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-15', 'Broken bulb Product would have been find had it not arrived with a cracked bulb. It had already broken down all the boxes when I noticed the defect, so it wasn\'t worth the hassle of shipping it back and I just tossed it and will order another. Frustrating!'),
(7105, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-16', 'Highly recommended - a great coffeemaker! It\'s great!  I use it as an alarm clock, awakening to the soft sounds and delicious smell of brewing coffee that permeates my little house.  I like the detachable water container, which I can take off, fill from my Britta water filter, and put back on. The brewing temperature is lower than what I used to, but probably the temperature that my Aeropress recommends.  The warmer is a higher temperature, so by the time I shower and pour the first cup, it\'s piping hot, which I like. This is by far the best coffeemaker I have ever owned, which includes Brauns, Cuisinarts, Mr. Coffees, and more that I can\'t remember. Highly recommended!'),
(7106, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-14', 'great little toaster oven Works well--only thing is that timer dial is hard to turn back--must turn past 10--no problem, but when turning back if you want it to run under 10, it is hard. This is difficult for me because I have lost a lot of strength in my hands (I\'m almost 70).  Also a little disappointed because the pans I bought to use in it didn\'t fit--but okay I\'ll use them in the regular oven.  A fan of B & D.'),
(7107, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-21', 'A Great Little Coffee Pot and the Price is Very Fair This is a really good coffee pot. I like the little wheels which allow me to jockey it around when I\'m filling it with water and coffee. It makes very tasty coffee and is easy to keep clean. I think it\'s a fine buy for the money.'),
(7108, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-23', 'Makes a great cup of coffee in seconds - and I need it quick in the AM! I did not purchase this from Amazon. I actually did not purchase this at all. I ordered a K40 machine and they were out of stock so I received this in it\'s place. I am glad I did as I love this brewer. I love being able to select the size and strength of my coffee. I almost always use the 10oz setting and strong setting. It works fine with the San Francisco Bay coffee that I buy right here on Amazon. The only reason for 4 stars instead of five is the water reservoir being in the back. It may not matter to you but in my case because where I keep my machine it makes filling it a bit of a pain where my older K40 was very easy to remove and fill. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7109, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'Five Stars Great coffee maker and we use it all the time'),
(7110, 5, 1, 4, '2014-01-25', 'It does the trick The Good:  Removable water container, no drip mess from the carafe and the easy pop out coffee holder. The bad:  Looks like a cheap piece of s@@@ Overall: It works and has a few features I like.  I am sure I will replace it in a bit but it was inexpensive and makes coffee.'),
(7111, 8, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Five Stars It is perfect for my needs!'),
(7112, 12, 1, 4, '2014-11-19', 'Tried and True This is a tried and true product for me -- it\'s fairly inexpensive as toaster ovens go and after 3-4 years of daily family use it basically wears out so I buy another one. If it lasted longer (say 5+ years) I\'d give it 5/5 stars. Great value for the money -- toasts well and the mini-oven has an excellent thermostat.'),
(7113, 7, 3, 2, '2015-01-21', 'I do but don\'t recommend this. It says in the description \" The Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffeemaker allows the flexibility of brewing freshly ground coffee one minute\". That is not true! It took almost 5 minutes for an 8oz cup. If you are NOT looking for a 1 minute cup brew, then it may be for you. Also, my coffee mugs are 4 1/2 inches tall and will not fit on the Multilevel Cup Rest. Very disappointed overall. I was looking for a less expensive coffeemaker that the Keurig and guess I got what I paid for!!! I will probably return this and buy the Keurig.'),
(7114, 3, 1, 3, '2015-05-05', 'It was the best and it lasted eight years I bought this toaster oven after my first one died ): It was the best and it lasted eight years!! So of course I wanted the same model. Well they don\'t make that model anymore so this was the closest one. And it lasted maybe six months! it\'s junk I\'m so disappointed ):'),
(7115, 2, 1, 1, '2015-02-15', 'Toast got on fire and burned. Smoke every where ... Toast got on fire and burned.Smoke every where. scary...'),
(7116, 12, 1, 5, '2016-03-23', 'Great product Love it.  Very versatile'),
(7117, 12, 1, 5, '2016-12-10', 'Great little toaster oven This one is for the RV. Still using the one in the house. Great little toaster oven.'),
(7118, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Did not like Keurig prices and this alternative is more than half the price.'),
(7119, 6, 1, 5, '2016-08-04', 'Five Stars Do it\'s job.'),
(7120, 2, 1, 1, '2015-08-29', 'Just tried it for the first time --- even on ... Just tried it for the first time --- even on the first use and lowest heat, it overheats and starts to burn food immediately. I had to unplug it and close the toaster oven door to make sure there is no fire. Not sure what to do and my return window has already closed.'),
(7121, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-25', 'He Loves It. Was a gift for my husband, and he loves it.'),
(7122, 2, 1, 5, '2015-10-16', '5 stars! My favorite item in the kitchen! i love the fact that this not burn my morning toast as well as my evening pizza when heated unlike the previous oven that I used which did such! Very ergonomic too!'),
(7123, 7, 3, 1, '2016-09-18', 'I bought this Hamilton beach flexbrew single serve coffee maker to replace my keurig that died on me. I chose this machine to save money vs get a new keurig. The price was my deciding factor at $59.99 The flexbrew worked great for about a month (the time it took me to lose my receipt), then all the problems started. The main and biggest problem is when using ground coffee (and no I\'m not using too much coffee as there is fill line in the basket) it overflows in the carafe spilling coffee grounds in ur cup of coffee and down the side of the machine. The grounds also get in the rubber sealing ring around the needle where they further drip into the water reservoir upon opening the lid. A nightmare to clean for each cup u wager to make. Next problem is about 50% of the time the machine fails to start brewing. I have to unplug it and plug it back in to get it to start (sometimes several times) which is annoying, especially when I\'m running late. Third problem is u never know how much coffee you\'ll actually get in ur cup no matter if u put enough water in for a full cup or not (of course I always go for a full cup though with fingers crossed.) And the last problem is sometimes the coffee isn\'t even hot enough to dissolve powdered creamer which makes for an awful cup of coffee. I prefer my coffee hot and my creamer dissolved. For me, this flexbrew just makes me miss my keurig :( I will never buy another hamilton beach coffee maker. Saving for another keurig now since at least I know it\'ll work for the money. You know..... get what u pay for and all.'),
(7124, 1, 1, 2, '2015-10-17', 'because I liked the first one and it lasted us a couple ... This is my second Keurig, because I liked the first one and it lasted us a couple years, I decided to buy another.  Imagine my suprise when I went to used a kcup that I purchased from Amazon, and my new computerized Keurig would not accept it.  It would not allow me to brew my coffee. Turns out unauthorized kcups or rebel kcups, will not work in the coffee maker.  It has something to do with recongnizing the ink on the top label of the kcup.  I searched online to find a resolution and found you need to peel off the top label of a used authorized kcup and place in on top of the rebel kcup.  When I ordered the coffeemaker, I don\'t recall reading anything about not accepting all kcups. So, for that reason I am rating it low.'),
(7125, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-21', 'I especially like the feature that allows you extend the bread above ... The toaster works well. I especially like the feature that allows you extend the bread above the toaster for easy removal. The settings are functional, Cancel mode is a feature I have used often  . The toast slots are wide enough to toast thicker bread slices and split rolls even hot dog and hamburger  buns.'),
(7126, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-06', 'Best I have ever had After reading about 500 coffee maker reviews I got this one. I had a cuisinart and the heating pad broke. I always had my coffee setting on bold to get more coffee flavor. Wow, I set this HB to bold and it was the strongest coffee I had ever had. I had to just put it on regular after that. And that just means my other coffee maker was doing a poor job. It took me two weeks to stop pulling this coffee maker out from under the cabinets from habit. The separate fill tank is great! Just turn the unit and pull out. A few people compained about not getting the last drop out because of the lip on the pot, well, it is a drop, maybe two that you can\'t get, geez. I prefer the no stray coffee grounds to losing a drop of coffee. And the bright light people don\'t like, it looks as bright as everything else in my kitchen, oven, microwave, hood, fridge... pretty soon I won\'t even have to turn the light on. Great coffee maker, I am 100% happy with it. And the price and performance are great.'),
(7127, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-27', 'Five Stars works great and with the permanent filter I am ready to brew away.'),
(7128, 8, 1, 5, '2015-07-03', 'Does it\'s job Works great'),
(7129, 4, 1, 1, '2015-09-03', 'Beware, No Timer! Note there is no timer on this Toaster Oven for Baking, Broiling or other purposes, which presents a safety issue. I have never encountered a Toaster Oven without one.'),
(7130, 6, 1, 5, '2014-04-18', 'Best Toaster I\'ve had in years Best Toaster I\'ve had in years.  It handles everything from bread to bagels, and toasts everything according to the toast range selected.'),
(7131, 9, 1, 1, '2015-02-06', 'Machine looks nice, but Cuisinart\'s customer service is not a good look. This coffee pot will eventually fail, but the true failure is the Cuisinart\'s horrific customer service.  I bought this coffee pot because it looked so sleek, but looks are not everything.  I thought the company who made the product would stand behind it, but the 3 year warranty means nothing when a company completely ignores it\'s customers.  After 2 weeks of attempting to get support I give up, I\'ll support a different company from now on.'),
(7132, 6, 1, 2, '2014-10-29', 'Two Stars Toasts nicely, but large slices (homemade bread) are too wide and you have to cut the slices in half.'),
(7133, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-19', 'Great coffee maker! We love this, you can program it the night before, it looks great on the counter, and it has a separate water holder that easily detaches for filling. We liked it so much we bought a second one for our second home!'),
(7134, 12, 1, 3, '2015-01-16', 'cheap but does save space Saves countertop space and in our case added a toaster oven to our kitchen, but the oven is very small (barely fits a single piece of pizza) and the toaster function toasts unevenly.  It is a cheaply made product and likely won\'t last long.  As I remember it was not that expensive, and you get what you pay for.'),
(7135, 12, 1, 3, '2016-01-28', 'Three Stars nice'),
(7136, 10, 1, 4, '2016-01-12', 'Four Stars Super cheap and does the job really well!!'),
(7137, 3, 1, 5, '2014-09-04', 'B&D Always Lives Up To Expectation Replacing B&D Dine In which has been dependable for don\'t know how many years. The only real problem started earlier this year - must unplug to turn off. Appliance repair guy said can\'t find switches anymore. Love new. First convection, so bit of learning curve. Recommend.'),
(7138, 5, 1, 2, '2016-09-29', 'Just try to replace the carafe! This was an acceptable, if not great coffee maker, for about 6 months when for reasons I don\'t understand the unusually thin glass of the carafe developed a hairline crack and leaked.  Here\'s what earns a failing rating:  there are no replacement carafes for this model of coffee maker on the market!  Not from Hamilton, (on whose website the item is noted to be \"out of stock,\" - a term often obscuring \"discontinued\"), not through Amazon, not through any third-party re-seller.  Consequently, even if this was the finest coffee maker of its kind on the market, which it isn\'t, it is now utterly unusable and worthless.'),
(7139, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-20', 'So Far So Good, just took it out of boxed cleaned it ... So Far So Good, just took it out of boxed cleaned it up and brewed my first pot.  Delicious, easy to use.  Very basic looking, replacing my Mr. Coffee that was leaking, just put new countertops in afraid of hot water leaking and ruining my new investment.  This sits up so it\'s not directly on the surface.  Shipped quick and undamaged.'),
(7140, 8, 1, 4, '2015-12-10', 'Does as advertised, coffee +++ Power switch stiff and needs major push to operate, moving the product across the counter but otherwise a good buy and makes a decient cup of coffee.'),
(7141, 2, 1, 4, '2015-06-07', 'Shocking poor quality from Black and Decker Nice product for the money.'),
(7142, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-05', 'Awesome Oven Purchased about two months ago after my brother recommended it.  Kids are all gone now, so just my wonderful wife and I.  We remodeled our home 3 years ago and installed double wall oven, but to cook just for the two of us it was a waste of energy.  So far we a extremely pleased.  Has several features; bagel is great, convection oven works perfectly, toaster, etc.  Great value!'),
(7143, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-14', 'Good old toaster oven Just what I hoped it would be. I hate bells and whistles on appliances. Toast time is a little slow, though'),
(7144, 9, 1, 5, '2015-04-08', 'Cuisinart DCC-3000 Coffee-on-Demand 12-Cup Coffee Maker I am not a \"pod person\". I want a whole pot of coffee that dispenses a cup at the touch of a button. This coffee maker does just that. It\'s great!'),
(7145, 4, 1, 5, '2015-10-17', 'Very nice. High quality and easy to use Very nice.  High quality and easy to use.  Love the feature of the rack automatically advancing as you open the door!'),
(7146, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-17', 'My first one only lasted 20 years+ This is my second Black and Decker toaster oven.  The first one only lasted 20+ years before the toaster automatic feature stopped working.  I could still use it manually, but opted to replace it instead.  The new one is larger and works like a champ.'),
(7147, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-23', 'Great product! Can\'t beat a Black+Decker.  Great product!s'),
(7148, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-27', 'Five Stars Love it so much!! Makes great coffee!!.'),
(7149, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-14', 'Five Stars good'),
(7150, 3, 1, 3, '2015-06-13', '... curve for the various settings the oven will be fine and fits well in the space on my counter ... I think when I master the learning curve for the various settings the oven will be fine and fits well in the space on my counter under my cabinets.  Still working with the settings and find the labels difficult to read.  Also the end of time bell is extremely weak, and I can\'t hear it even if I am right there in the kitchen.  Oven does get extremely hot so this is also a factor to be mentioned in my review of the product.  One positive thing for me is that the glass door is at eye level so I can check on items being cooked without having to open door or get down on my knees to see into my stove oven.  All in all I will give this three stars and will get much use of the oven during the upcoming hot summer.'),
(7151, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-27', 'This coffee maker is great. I like that the water tank is removable ... This coffee maker is great. I like that the water tank is removable so that you can just take it over to the sink. The coffee comes out tasting very good. It\'s a great unit.'),
(7152, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-15', 'Five Stars Great little oven.'),
(7153, 12, 1, 5, '2016-01-11', 'Once I get the temps down it will be a perfect little machine This runs REALLY hot. If you have it on the highest heat for the toaster oven section it will be black in 3 minutes. Once I get the temps down it will be a perfect little machine. It looks cute and so nice on my counter compared to other toaster ovens. The toaster section works good for regular bread but, some of the stuff gets folded or bent in there making it hard to remove and to use. Overall I love it because it is nice enough looking to leave out on the counter.'),
(7154, 6, 1, 1, '2015-06-11', 'How about a refund or credit? NEVER fully toasted bread, waffles, or bagels. The stamped lettering wiped off when cleaning. I tossed it last week. It is junk. Now I come to find the product is under review by Amazon. How about a refund or credit? BTW: I bought a Hamilton Beach toaster this week to replace the Cuisinart. It toasts great, as any well made toaster should.'),
(7155, 9, 1, 4, '2015-06-08', 'Now if it will just last.... Great machine so far.'),
(7156, 12, 1, 1, '2015-03-03', 'The oven temp knob (which is the on/off control) turns so easily that I have found it running several times after ... This toaster oven is worthless. Oven door doesn\'t close completely. Anything thicker than a slice of thin crust pizza burns.Toast burns on the bottom but not toasted on top.Crumbs collect in a groove under oven door and getting them out without taking the unit to the sink to wipe down,cut my finger.The oven temp knob (which is the on/off control)  turns so easily that I have found it running several times after accidentally touching the knob when cleaning the counter. Mine is in the recycling bin!'),
(7157, 3, 1, 5, '2016-02-03', 'Great Oven !! I have never had a toaster oven before and thought it would not be worth giving up the counter space.  How wrong I was.  I use the oven every day and most days several times a day.  I had forgotten how good cheese and cinnamon toasts were.  The oven heats up quickly and holds the temperature very well.  My big iron skillet cornbread pan even fits in it nicely !!  I am very pleased and I would recommend it.'),
(7158, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-24', 'Perfect for a person living on there own! Perfect for one person that wants to filla cup and a thermos to go!.'),
(7159, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-29', 'Five Stars Love it.'),
(7160, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-28', 'and I really do like it. It makes a good cup of coffee I have wanted a Keurig since I had my first cup of coffee from the original model many years ago, but I could never get myself to spend the money on a coffee maker.  I got married this last summer and finally got one, and I really do like it.  It makes a good cup of coffee, has a lot of features that allow you to choose the strength and size of the cup, and can even brew a 40(?)oz pot of coffee if you get the correct K-cups.  There are a few things that keep me from giving a 5-star rating, however. While I am happy I didn\'t have to buy the actual machine, it is unfortunate having to spend $10-$15 for a 16 count of K-cups (obviously depending on the brand and where you purchase them) when you can buy a canister of grounds from the supermarket for $8.  Also, it can be quite difficult to find the K-cups that are for the pot in a typical supermarket, and even when you do, there isn\'t much flavor variety.  Overall, however, I am happy with my Keurig.  Plus, they gave me free pods for writing a review! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(7161, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'I love my Keurig Brewing system I love my Keurig Brewing system. I got it for college and use it everyday. I feature with the Hot Cocoa or other is a lovely feature.Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for the review!'),
(7162, 3, 1, 5, '2015-10-07', 'Five Stars Good quality'),
(7163, 6, 1, 4, '2016-01-08', 'new owner appears to like it. only complaint was that it had a ... unit given as a gift.  new owner appears to like it. only complaint was that it had a tendency to burn toast on one side while the other remained slightly browned.'),
(7164, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-08', 'I LOVE being able to lift the water reservoir off the ... I LOVE being able to lift the water reservoir  off the back side of this machine.  Pouring water into coffee machines from the caref/container was always the most annoying part of making coffee. being able to set the heat temp can keep the coffee from burning over a longer period of time. the \"Bold\" setting takes longer to make - but you can use fewer grounds to achieve the desired darkness (saves $$), and if you like really dark coffee this setting is a game changer!'),
(7165, 9, 1, 3, '2016-04-09', 'Ok Coffee Maker Makes coffee ok but, warmer (inside) does not maintain a high enough temperature.'),
(7166, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-15', 'Love it I love this toaster oven. I used to always have a bread toaster because, let\'s face it\' toaster ovens don\'t toast bread very well. I now have much more counterspace since it is a toaster and toaster oven. Highly recommend.'),
(7167, 12, 1, 1, '2016-01-26', 'Not the best deal. Too small for anything, and they asked me to pay for shipping it back. Not the best deal.'),
(7168, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-14', 'Five Stars Love it! Clock/timer is a great feature.'),
(7169, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-19', 'Five Stars Makes hot delicious coffee'),
(7170, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-03', 'Buy it.. A great little appliance.'),
(7171, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-01', 'It\'s a toaster oven. It\'s a toaster oven that works as a toaster oven should. Looks nice too.'),
(7172, 5, 1, 4, '2014-02-03', 'Great simple coffee maker. I got rid of my 12 year old basic coffee maker for this - this is a great coffee maker with 2 exceptions:  1) cord needs to be about 6inches longer 2) the warming option - has 3 settings but I still find the lowest setting too hot - I still need to instead just turn of the coffee maker off altogether after it\'s done - heat kills flavor, wish they had an even lower (by half on lowest) setting than what they do.'),
(7173, 5, 1, 5, '2016-07-15', 'Five Stars I really like this coffee maker. For the price, it is one of the best.'),
(7174, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-14', 'Always a fresh cup... Shouldn\'t have waited so long to buy one of these for home.  Hard to keep fresh coffee going in a one person home and I was making new pots and wasting money trying to do so.  This solves that problem...'),
(7175, 10, 1, 2, '2015-12-04', 'Starting to second guess Amazon! Bought this on Oct 18th and the motor burned out already (Dec 1st). This item is no longer eligible for return either.  Terrible!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(7176, 9, 1, 1, '2016-07-18', 'Great for coloring cabinets and flooring a nice shade of coffee One star, only because less isn\'t possible. Let\'s talk first about what it\'s supposed to do; make coffee. It isn\'t the world\'s greatest coffee maker, but it\'s good enough. Looks nice and stylish on the counter. You can make 60oz of coffee (does anyone in the world drink a 5oz cup of coffee??!). Tall mugs fit underneath if you remove the drip tray, and travel mugs fit if you pull it to the end of the counter, remove the drip tray and then put the mug under (i.e, travel mugs don\'t fit). Here\'s the downside. It leaks. Not all of the time; that would be simple. But enough of the time that we need to leave a cup underneath it to catch the drips - the drip tray just doesn\'t hold enough. However; you can\'t trust a cup, even, because this useless thing will just empty itself into the cup, and then all over the floor. Just like today; I brewed 60oz, took 8oz for morning coffee, and left a cup underneath. Came back to the kitchen after an hour or so, and the coffee machine was empty; it had leaked coffee all over the counter, draw fronts and floor (stained the draw fronts, which means I need to work on them later and pray that I can remove the color). It\'s not water deposits, which is the only suggestion the manual gives, because we use filtered water. It\'s just a bad product design. I won\'t even take it to Savers or Goodwill, as I don\'t want anyone else to have the problem; it\'s headed straight for the trash.'),
(7177, 6, 1, 4, '2015-11-07', 'Great for bagels Great for bagels.  Only use it for that so cannot tell you anything about the toast, but I figure it would do just as well.  3.5 gives me a lightly golden brown bagel, my brother prefers a 4.5, much darker but not burnt.'),
(7178, 3, 1, 5, '2015-07-07', 'Good to go Love it, once I figured the timer...'),
(7179, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-14', 'Don\'t pass it up! This is this best coffee pot I\'ve owned. I\'ve had at least a dozen of the best that are found in Wally world. Every detail about it is awesome. The water container comes off the back to be filled. Then rinse out the pot and  the basket and your ready to go.  Even has little tiny wheels on the bottom to allow it turn very easy.'),
(7180, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-03', 'I love this little machine I love this little machine. For as low priced as this is, it packs in a punch. Makes great smoothies and margaritas! It has no problems with ice or frozen fruits.'),
(7181, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-16', 'The price is right. If you want a portable, sturdy smoothie maker, this one gets the job done! Also, the price is right.'),
(7182, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'Can\'t beat it for the price This is perfect for what I needed. A simple blender that I can make my morning smoothies with and take on the go. For the price you can\'t beat it!'),
(7183, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-11', 'love it! got this yesterday 3-10-16, love it !!  My old B & D just finally quit after 6 years of daily use, ordered this one and am very pleased with it.'),
(7184, 3, 1, 5, '2016-03-03', 'Five Stars Works perfect.....Love it.'),
(7185, 11, 1, 1, '2014-04-11', 'Burnt toast This toaster is a fire hazard. It burns toast constantly - but that\'s not even the dangerous part.  There is a dial that you turn when toasting the toast.  When you turn the toaster off it is so easy to accidentally turn the dial too far and  set it to the  \'always on\' setting.  This means the toaster never turns off and eventually burns your house down.  A setting like this is dangerous enough - but to have it so near the toaster dial is a fire waiting to happen.  We have three kids who make their own breakfast.  They are responsible kids.  But I can\'t let them use this because it would just  be too easy to make an awful mistake.  I am buying another toaster.'),
(7186, 8, 1, 3, '2016-08-26', 'Nice unit but you must let it finish before you ... Nice unit but you must let it finish before you can move the coffee pot or you will have a nice mess to clean up.'),
(7187, 11, 1, 1, '2014-05-11', 'THIS TOASTER OVEN IS A REAL WASTE OF MONEY!! Purchased this for $20.  Horrible item.  Stupid way to navigate how you want to toast.  Turn knobs every which way I don\'t have time to sit there and figure it out.  Smoke comes out.  Overheats.  Lousy toast.  Takes too long.  Very hot outside.  How can they get away with selling this.  I also purchased a B & D rice cooker that broke after a few months.  I won\'t be buying anything from them any more no matter how cheap.  I put it away and took out my old-fashioned toaster.  Way better.  I feel stupid even leaving a single star.  They should put a symbol for \"Dud\" on these scales.  Because that\'s what this is!'),
(7188, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-25', 'Birthday Present for Mom Bought this for my mom for her birthday. Going by what she said, she said it is very beautiful looking. She also stated that when she cooked chicken tenders in it, that it made them really fast. She lives in Florida, so I can\'t see it for myself, but she seems very happy about it. She was even stunned that there was a toaster and toaster oven combination. I am happy with the purchase for her.'),
(7189, 9, 1, 5, '2016-12-12', 'So Glad We Bought This! This is a beautiful machine!  At first, we were worried about the short cord (about 12\") and it certainly wouldn\'t reach any outlets we had.  I tugged on the cord and there was a lot of resistance, but I pulled a little harder and it came out to about 3\' (or so).  It might have had to go back if the cord hadn\'t extended, so glad I tugged a little harder! Had a little trouble figuring out which way the coffee basket goes in, but it may not matter, because the coffee brewed and the instructions said it would not if the basket was in the wrong way. I cleaned the inside as directed and made a pot of coffee, it was delicious and a very hearty flavor, much better than our old Mr. Coffee. This will work out great for our Christmas guests and it seems to keep the coffee hot for a very long time (so far 3 hours).'),
(7190, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-15', 'Great Coffee Maker Purchased for my oldest daughter in college.  she has used it to make coffee and ramen noodles every college students must haves.  Makes the perfect amount of coffee for her before class or while studying.  Easy to clean.'),
(7191, 3, 1, 4, '2015-05-17', 'Four Stars Works great and saves a lot of time.'),
(7192, 1, 1, 2, '2015-06-06', 'INSERT COFFEE, ADD DRAMA Coffee makers should not be political statements, but I\'m afraid that Keurig is becoming more well-known for their ridiculous (and futile) use of DRM (Digital Rights Management) to limit the types of coffee you are allowed to make than they are for the quality of their coffee makers these days. Why on earth this new model will not allow you to use brands of coffee that would work with their previous unit just boggles my mind. This makes the new unit more like a downgrade than an upgrade. Why would anyone pay more money to brew fewer types of coffee? The 2.0 model has no new, useful features to speak of over the 1.0 model, so I really do not see the point of anyone wanting the new model. If you like your Keurig 1.0, I keep it. On the upside, the Keurig (still) makes an excellent cup of coffee and is definitely less work than old-fashioned coffee makers. I am used to brewing an entire pot at a time though and without having to pay extra for their proprietary carafe, doing so is simply impossible. Honestly, I just don\'t see this ever replacing a regular coffee maker in my home. It takes up too much space and makes far too little coffee (and fewer types of coffee) for me to switch.'),
(7193, 7, 3, 5, '2014-01-24', 'So happy i bought it'),
(7194, 8, 1, 5, '2014-07-11', 'Five Stars I love it'),
(7195, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'Works well and very reasonable. We have used this a lot since purchase.  Price was very reasonable and it serves the purpose.  Nice size, not too big.  Works fine for us.'),
(7196, 7, 3, 4, '2016-04-27', 'v ery cute little coffee maker. just right for me. i love coffee.'),
(7197, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-02', 'That is pretty good. Performs as advertised.  That is pretty good.'),
(7198, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-01', 'Great little toaster oven Great little toaster oven. Works well to re-heat pizza, cook fish and brown a small amount of fries without heating up your kitchen. You must remember to close off the toaster part with a slider device, otherwise the oven part won\'t work well. Wish there was a little more height to get larger items in the oven, but then I suppose it would take up too much counter space.'),
(7199, 6, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'Five Stars Great little toaster.  The openings allow for the larger pieces of bread.  Toasts beautifully.'),
(7200, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'Best coffeemaker EVER!!! Love, love, love our new Keurig 2.0! Everything about the experience of using this coffeemaker is wonderful!  It\'s fast, fresh and easy to clean up.'),
(7201, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-07', 'Excellent Excellent'),
(7202, 1, 1, 5, '2016-03-06', 'LOVE. IT I. LOVE. IT!!!!!'),
(7203, 5, 1, 1, '2016-02-15', 'The first one we had brewed fine, but the minute button broke after a couple ... We have had two in two months. The first one we had brewed fine, but the minute button broke after a couple weeks. Returned that one and decided to try another one. The third day we had it the face plate where the buttons are just popped off. Too bad, the coffee was good and nice and hot. But piece of junk. Not buying another one.'),
(7204, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-06', 'Easy to operate (after you read the instructions) Having had a Keurig brewer for many years my wife and I are sold on them.  After 10 years of heavy use our previous brewer was beginning to die. I failed to realize that Keurig had updated their technology during that time.  I plugged in this brewer and started pushing buttons like I did on the previous brewer and was disappointed that it didn\'t work. My wife urged me read and follow the instructions and I was soon rewarded with an exceptional cup of coffee.  Some of the other things I like about this brewer is it tells you when it needs cleaning and the cleaning liquid is provided with the brewer. Also, the water reservoir is better than our older model.  We did find that the Melitta cups that worked in our previous Keurig brewer do not work in this brewer (they are a bit short).  This does not detract from the great cup of coffee you get using the K-Cup designated coffee.  We like this coffee brewer.'),
(7205, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-27', 'Five Stars ok'),
(7206, 3, 1, 5, '2014-10-20', 'Five Stars It is fantastic!!!'),
(7207, 4, 1, 5, '2016-02-05', 'Five Stars A+++ Product!!!'),
(7208, 12, 1, 5, '2014-02-09', 'Love this toaster This is a great toaster & toaster oven for people with limited counter space.  We\'ve been using it for a while, and have had no problems.  Pretty small toaster oven (1-2 slices of pizza), but we can\'t fit anything bigger, so we\'re glad to have it!  IDK what someone meant by \"no cancel button\" -- there\'s definitely one on the unit...'),
(7209, 5, 1, 2, '2014-12-12', 'seemed like a positive feature Read the reviews and everyone had such positive feedback.  The problem I experienced is the burner does not heat the coffee hot, it does not brew the coffee hot as some other brands I have used in the past.  Someone mentioned the coffee does not burn when left on the burner, seemed like a positive feature, for  I did have coffee makers that burned the coffee when left on the burner, but I would rather have a hot cup of coffee initially  and shut the machine off after the brew than a cup of coffee that lacks the hotness.  I also thought to give it at least 10 minutes more time on the hot plate, but it didn\'t matter.  .'),
(7210, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-20', 'GREAT TOASTER Having recently received my new Cuisinart CPT-122, I now truly appreciate toast, bagels and English muffins again. This simple, inexpensive toaster is terrific. I highly recommend this toaster.'),
(7211, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-09', 'Five Stars Great coffee pot!  Bought it for my office and everyone loves it!'),
(7212, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-20', 'Good buy! I love this toaster oven! It works really well & as long as you don\'t set the toasting option too high the toast comes out evenly toasted.  I use it mostly in the summer when I don\'t want to heat up my kitchen with my large oven. Heats up food quickly.'),
(7213, 7, 3, 5, '2016-05-22', 'This great lil machine is good for the single person and single cups of coffee. Works with very many different types of k-cups as well as regular ground coffee. Can\'t beat it for the price.'),
(7214, 11, 1, 2, '2015-02-10', 'Cannot recommend Black & Decker any longer We have owned several B&D toaster ovens over the years, but this will probably be the last. Older models help up well, however the B&D name no longer stands for quality appliances as it once did. We used this model regularly, but it was never abused in any way. Today after just eight months, it gave up the spirit - no longer eligible for return; destined for the trash. What a shame.'),
(7215, 11, 1, 5, '2014-01-04', 'toaster oven -was a gift for grandson choose because of a good name brand and th many things that you can use it for. Also good size'),
(7216, 7, 3, 5, '2016-06-10', 'Makes my tea or coffee from the grounds. Don\'t need the expensive single cup packs,,,,'),
(7217, 1, 1, 4, '2015-09-11', 'Great product for everyday use. I was really excited to get a Keurig for it\'s convenience. I had a traditional coffee pot brewer and would often only brew coffee on the weekends because of the time it would take to brew a whole pot. The Keurig fixes that with no problem, it makes it so easy to get fresh coffee in no time. I use it almost every day and my 1 wish is that it had a 12 oz option so that it get more coffee per cup. However, I do like the fact that it include a \"Strong\" option so that you can make your cup stronger if you want. I think this model is smaller and more compact than the previous ones i have seen, which is nice because I don\'t have a lot of counter space to spare. I like the fact that the reservoir is detachable which makes it easy to fill up without a lot of maneuvering and effort. A few quick points. Don\'t purchase the \"strawberry\" color thinking it\'s going to be red it\'s NOT red it is definitely a lighter color. The preheating takes a little longer than I would expect, but overall it\'s still faster than brewing a full coffee pot. I didn\'t want to spring the extra money for the carafe but I like the fact that it has a option to brew for more than one person. Overall i think it\'s a great buy. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7218, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-14', 'Only one drawback.... Very Happy Overall Now that I\'ve been using it for several days, I\'m happy to share my overall opinion of the new Keurig 2.0 Brewer I love that I can brew a carafe, and the design is sleeker and takes up less space on my counter.  I also love that it\'s WAY easier to take apart to clean and comes with detailed cleaning instructions.  Touch screen is pretty cool, not totally necessary, but makes it possible for them to give you more choices (like the bold brew option.... nice touch!) Biggest con is them forcing me into certain brands of coffee.  It\'s not up to Keurig to decide the best quality coffee for me. I\'m smart enough to figure out what I like. This irritation is enhanced by the fact that I can\'t even use my My K-Cup Reusable Brewer with the system.  It\'s poor planning to not even be able to use a Keurig Brand accessory with my new Keurig. Lucky for me I\'m not the only person that feels this way by a long shot and several consumers and coffee companies are more than happy to share their tips tricks and work arounds on that front. So... overall I\'m a big fan of my new 2.0 Brewer, and feel like the pros combined with the convenience of my Keurig and ingenuity of other consumers help over come the drawbacks of the new machine. Looking forward to saying Hello Keurig every day!  I got this brewer for free from Influenster\' for testing and review:'),
(7219, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Hamilton beach toaster We really like it'),
(7220, 1, 1, 3, '2015-08-27', 'Just okay The 2.0 is simply just okay.  This is what Keurig gave us as a replacement when our Vue stopped working.  I had a lot of Vue pods left that are now unusable as the Vue is discontinued.  Keurig did however replace with new pods for the 2.0 so no complaints with customer service!  I can no longer make a 16 ounce cup without pushing 10 ounce and 6 ounce... just a minor inconvenience though.  Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(7221, 5, 1, 4, '2015-07-31', 'Happy customer Very good machine, we are very happy with it.'),
(7222, 10, 1, 3, '2015-12-02', 'Decent blender for the price Well, this is certainly a case of you get what you pay for. This will do fine for small breakfast shakes or the such. However, you need a decent amount of liquid for it to blend at all, and if you blend for an extended period it will start to smell pretty burnt. Overall, decent for the price, but I wouldn\'t get it again.'),
(7223, 9, 1, 4, '2015-02-23', 'Very nice! Just got my new machine and am pleased, 3 things pointed out in other reviews of possible problems were all ok except one. First the problem with the charcoal filter fitting properly didn\'t exist the filter seated nicely in its place, net the power wire had plenty of length to anable pulling the Machine out from under my cabinets to fill aprox 16\" worth. And last the only glitch I saw was the gauge for the amount of coffee in the resovoir but with a gentle knuckle knock below gauge window the neddlle move to it proper position, not a problem for me . My first batch of coffee came out a little weak but will re adjust amount of grinds for nest brew. The coffee came out hot and took aprox 7 mins.i will update on this product in the future for any issues.'),
(7224, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-02', 'I love this. The separate water reservoir makes it easy ... I love this. The separate water reservoir makes it easy and spill free. It is easy to use and program as well. There is a light when you push the button to pour so you can see how full your mug is getting, and he gauge makes it easy to know how much coffee is left! I was so happy to replace my old coffee maker with this gem!'),
(7225, 1, 1, 2, '2016-09-06', 'As soon as I switch back to the reusable filter it works perfectly fine (so, there is no clogged needle or anything) It works OK with the reusable filter that I purchased separately, but except the first two times it does not work with Keurig Kcups. Every time I try to use the Kcup it is giving me the same message \"water under pressure\" and that I might need to clean the needle. As soon as I switch back to the reusable filter it works perfectly fine (so, there is no clogged needle or anything). I\'ve already thrown away 6 Kcups trying, same message every time. What a big disappointment ! I had stocked up on Kcup pods and now I am unable to use them. I hope someone from the company is reading this and reaches out with a solution, it is probably a common issue, otherwise will return.'),
(7226, 4, 1, 5, '2016-10-04', 'Five Stars Best little toaster oven,very happy with my purchase.'),
(7227, 11, 1, 4, '2014-08-27', 'I Am Happy With This I had an Oster toaster oven for years and loved it.  One day it just stopped working and I was not able to find the same or similar model so I found this Black and Decker.  It is small, but I use it for toast only and it works fine so far.  The price was a no-brainer.'),
(7228, 6, 1, 3, '2016-11-15', 'Basic toaster It does a decent job toasting, the heating elements heat a bit unevenly but it gets the job done and works well for a basic toaster.  Its worked well for a year for me without any issues so far.'),
(7229, 2, 1, 1, '2015-04-19', 'Doesn\'t toast evenly, has no \'set it and forget it\' darkness setting, confusing controls. I quit using it. This toaster is a POS.  There is only one heating element on top and bottom, where my old similar Black & Decker toaster had two.  This means it wouldn\'t toast evenly.  CHEAP.  Even if it had toasted properly, there is only a \"timer dial\" to toast.  You can\'t set your ideal toast settings and just push a lever each time afterwards like every other toaster I\'ve ever used.  No, you have to just turn the dial to about roughly where you turned it to last time.  Worst user interface ever.  I honestly can\'t believe how highly rated this horrible toaster is.  I quit using it and bought a different toaster.'),
(7230, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-29', 'Small handy coffee maker Small size, just right.'),
(7231, 10, 1, 1, '2015-09-27', 'Save yourself frustration and get something better. I thought I would give it a try based on so many positive reviews here. First time I went to use it, the bottom seal gave way and it started to pour out from the bottom. I sent it back.'),
(7232, 6, 1, 1, '2014-08-12', 'so many good reviews I had to order it so many good reviews I had to order it. The toaster has wires inside that glow when it is heating. Most of them on the inside walls did not light up and it only toasted on one side of the bread. I sent it back and ordered another thinking I had a lemon. Second on did the same thing. I sent it back also.'),
(7233, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-26', 'Five Stars I Love it.'),
(7234, 5, 1, 1, '2014-09-21', 'This didn\'t work for me.... It ... This didn\'t work for me....It was noisy at the start of the perking process and the gurgling sound troubled me so I returned it.'),
(7235, 1, 1, 3, '2016-01-19', 'Three Stars Clogs up easily u'),
(7236, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'I love mine! Gave as a gift but I have one as well.  Perfect for 1 person smoothies.  Very handy and efficient.  Also it\'s a great space saver - doesn\'t take up anymore room than a large cup.'),
(7237, 12, 1, 5, '2015-06-01', 'This does a great job and has wide slots on top for toasting ... This is my kind of toaster/oven... versatile and really neat! Why heat up a whole large oven for small items? This does a great job and has wide slots on top for toasting bagels and such.'),
(7238, 8, 1, 4, '2016-02-20', 'Compact and functional Good useful yet compact coffee maker. Small footprint. Pretty basic, no bells or whistles. Easy to keep clean.'),
(7239, 3, 1, 5, '2014-07-14', 'Black and Decker Oven!! Love it!! Works great. I need to get used to the way it cooks but so far so good. I love the preheat, oven off, and digital touchpad.  Will update after I\'ve had it awhile and can speak of it\'s longevity. Tried 3 Osters first and they wouldn\'t hold the temperature or get hot enough to broil. UPDATE: Toaster oven lasted 1 year and then stopped working. It was intermittent at first (the touch buttons did not respond). Then it quit altogether. This oven should have lasted longer than 1 year. Not happy with this at all. Second Update: After sending them my cut off oven power cord plus $7.50 Spectrum sent me a new oven in about a week. Happy Camper! This oven gets used daily. It even bakes pizza great. Wonderful and i couldn\'t live without it.'),
(7240, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-21', 'Love it but was sent different color which really sucked Love it but was sent different color which really sucked, as my kitchen is in a light minty green hue and I expected the color in the picture.'),
(7241, 3, 1, 4, '2014-11-16', 'The only drawback to this unit is the door- it ... The only drawback to this unit is the door- it has nothing to control or slow down the door as it opens, so it just opens all the way so quickly that the handle smacks against the counter if you\'re not prepared for it.'),
(7242, 5, 1, 2, '2015-09-01', 'Waste of money to buy what was suppose to be ... lasted three months then quit on us. Waste of money to buy what was suppose to be better quality.'),
(7243, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-10', 'Great travel blender. This is the perfect blender to take with you to work or use at home. It\'s only good for mixing the protein or dietary drinks with a little bit of fruit. It washes and stores very easily.'),
(7244, 1, 1, 5, '2016-08-23', 'Very Pleased Bought this on Amazon more than six months ago and still love it. Use filtered water in it and you will not have to use the provided filter and adapter.'),
(7245, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Awesome I love how versatile this brewer is. It looks so high tech and the glow it spreads is low light is awesome. I get me coffee fast and hot. It has so many features that I have yet to try. Awesome Awesome Awesome.'),
(7246, 11, 1, 1, '2014-01-19', 'Rating Black & Decker Toaster Oven was disappointed, since I had a B & D T. oven, just needed to replace it.  my reason is because the inside shelf/rack doesn\'t pull out with the oven door, as my other did.  This is very dangerous, and also, not easy to cook/toast/bake/grill, I wanted to return it.'),
(7247, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-14', 'For those who want quality Man o man....i bought this thing, thinking it would work ok...\'s t is, it\'s freaking awesome..and if your a coffee drinker...not having to pour the water in anymore your going to think your royalty'),
(7248, 4, 1, 4, '2015-05-02', 'Great toaster. One small drawback Great toaster.  One small drawback, toast is either too dark or too light.  Hard to adjust.'),
(7249, 7, 3, 1, '2016-09-20', 'I bought this 2 weeks ago and just died on me after 2 cups'),
(7250, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Great coffee maker Bought this for my husband and it is such a great coffee maker for individual cups of coffee since everyone that uses it like different coffee. I don\'t have to make multiple pots of coffee for just a few cups. The only thing I don\'t like about the Keurig is that it takes a few minutes in between each cup to make. Other than that it makes a great cup of coffee and very easy to use. I love the feature with how heavy of a brew that you want. I like it strong where my husband likes a more mellow cup of coffee.'),
(7251, 12, 1, 4, '2014-09-09', 'I like it Good product at a very good price. It arrived on time and in great condition.'),
(7252, 6, 1, 4, '2016-04-17', 'Cuisinart CPT-142 For a fill in while we replace our Breville Smart Oven - this product will do the trick'),
(7253, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-09', 'Great for the price Yes! My wife eats gluten free bread and the toasters offers a defrost setting and toast comes out perfect l!'),
(7254, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-22', 'Five Stars excellent machine'),
(7255, 9, 1, 5, '2015-08-09', 'This is MY coffee maker I had a Cuisinart for a long while.  When it needed to be replaced, I cheaped out and bought a rival brand.  Needless to say - I\'m back.  Bought a new Cuisinart & have relegated the Hamilton to the garage for the next church rummage sale.  Save money, get the Cuisinart to start.  And this is such an improvement to the individual cup servers.  If you have 3-4 people for coffee, you\'re standing at the machine while they visit.  This pot allows me to serve and sit.'),
(7256, 10, 1, 2, '2016-04-09', 'Two Stars Broke after about 10 uses'),
(7257, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-03', 'Good Product priced well. I dislike coffee machines to begin with, I view them all with a negative bias, my girlfriend however loves them, and was treated to Keurig recently that we returned as it did not cut it....We bought this and I have started to use it quite frequently. Makes a strong cup...I don\'t hate it. Good price.'),
(7258, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-09', 'Great Oven with a Great Price This is a great side oven. I hate turning on the oven in this \"hot\" weather and this convection oven works great to cook for the two of us. It does not heat up the kitchen nearly as much as the big oven and cooks great.  The Temps and Timing that are set are pretty standard but it is easy to change if need be. I would highly recommend the oven.  For the price it is a fantastic buy. Cathy.'),
(7259, 9, 1, 4, '2015-02-21', 'Nice, but has some flaws that need to be addressed. OK, gave it a fair 2-year period of use before writing this review.  They get an \'A\' for effort.  Has some nice features (removable fill tank, looks great, simple operation, etc).  So here is the downside:  Any finely ground (and some not so finely ground) coffee tends to float during coffee making process, and spills into coffee tank.  These grounds then get stuck in outflow mechanism, causing the the coffee to leak out of the dispensing spout.  Many days I have had to mop of a gigantic mess, and cant imagine what all this fluid has done to the integrity of my wood cabinets.  Second flaw - the coffee dispenses at a very slow pace sometimes.  Seems if you push down on coffee tank, you can speed that up.  So that indicates to me that the bucket is not sitting tight on outflow mechanism, and the lighter the coffee tank (the less full it is) the slower the coffee dispenses.  I like the machine, and am hoping someone at Cuisinart is monitoring these reviews to correct these flaws.  Until they do, however, I will be shopping for a different brand (my soaked cabinets and floors will not hold up for too much longer).'),
(7260, 6, 1, 4, '2014-03-02', 'Good toaster We have had the toaster for a couple of months now and it seems to be working great. It is not he fastest toaster but seems to toast evenly.'),
(7261, 3, 1, 4, '2016-01-11', 'Great toaster and oven- versatile, reliable A great replacement for our Cuisinart toaster oven which always burnt the toast. This toasts evenly, has a variety of settings and bakes evenly. It came with two sturdy pans.  It is much larger than we expected (our fault- we should have measured it out) and toasts more on one side than the other. It has a timer, which is great but you need to remember to re-start it if you are baking something for a long time, like potatoes. We are pleased with our purchase.'),
(7262, 6, 1, 5, '2016-04-12', 'Good product. Like it Got this toaster over the weekend. Good product. Like it.'),
(7263, 7, 3, 4, '2015-07-24', 'This machine just works fine and served my company very nice. No wasted coffee sitting in the pot!'),
(7264, 2, 1, 2, '2015-12-30', 'Only one height option for the tray It works good a little small but  The main thing that pisses me off is there\'s only one size where the tray could stay and when I put a bagel in or something that size it touches the fire and burnes it. you can\'t move the tray lower!  I wish you would be able to.'),
(7265, 12, 1, 3, '2014-04-27', 'Not as I expected Doesn\'t toast well.  Heating elements are too far away.  If the item is frozen, have to do it twice, on the hightest setting.'),
(7266, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'Great Coffee Maker for a Single Person Very happy so far- nice size for a smaller kitchen, easy to use, like the 1-4 cup option for myself, added water filter (extra purchase)'),
(7267, 5, 1, 4, '2014-12-20', 'we love this coffee maker we love this coffee maker. The only complaint is the pot is hard to get the very last bit of coffee out.'),
(7268, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-16', 'A good toaster at a good price I was attracted by the Cuisinart name and the fact that it was cheaper than my previous \"premium\" metal Oster toaster which was of quite poor quality.  Why spend big bucks if you get a shiny object that burns your toast and then the elements stop working?  So far this toaster does a good job of consistently making good, uniformly toasted bagels every morning.  Even the second bagel is OK without adjusting the setting (like with my old toaster). If I had to ding it a half a star it would be for the unusually shallow crumb tray, which makes a mess when the \"everything\" bagels shed larger bits.'),
(7269, 2, 1, 1, '2015-11-23', 'Ticking time bomb I\'ve been using this toaster for about 5 months and really dislike it. I hate the ticking noise it makes! And it is almost impossible to set the dial exactly right to get the toast the way you want it. Lastly I don\'t like that the toaster stays on when you open the door. My last one didn\'t. Very unhappy with this product.'),
(7270, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'My favorite Coffee Maker. This is my favorite coffee maker. I actually own three of them. The drip tray at the bottom can be removed if you need to fill a thermos or a to go cup. I can\'t imagine using any other coffee maker after using this one. The beep sound it makes to signal that the coffee is done or that the coffee maker has shut off is very low toned. Other coffee makers I have had in the past were extremely loud when they beeped. I am glad this one is quieter. It arrived in perfect condition and quickly.'),
(7271, 3, 1, 3, '2016-06-24', 'It\'s Large, Which is Great, But Other Than That, Not so Great This is the first time I\'ve used a Toaster Oven in years and years. I thought it was going to be the answer to my dreams.  We live in Florida and our house gets too hot inside in the summer, so i have set up a sort of \"mini kitchen\" out on the lanai with a crock pot, toaster oven, electric fry pan, etc. so that I can cook outside.  I found this toaster oven complicated to use all the features so i only use the Bake or Broil and the Timer.  Beyond that I couldn\'t seem to get it to work. The buttons seem flimsy and  I think it also cooks things too fast.  The top browns and it doesn\'t seem to cook especially evenly.  Also my baked potatoes took so long that I actually ate dinner before they were ready and had to fry them up for breakfast with my eggs the next morning to use them up. I do love that it is big enough to hold a large pie plate and most other baking dishes that I have.  In general, I am not thrilled with this product at all.  I think it is too expensive for what you get.  What really made me mad was that I was in Goodwill the other day and I saw one for $14.95!  I wish I had seen that one first because that\'s about all this one is worth, to me anyway!'),
(7272, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-13', '18 Months in and I love it! Like many reviewers I think this has to be one of the best coffemakers I have ever had experience with.  I\'m 61 so I\'ve seen a few come and go.  I have had mine 18 months and have zero complaints.  Neither the carafe nor the coffemaker drips, even when pulling the pot early, which I only did once to see what happens (don\'t see why people do that actually).  Basket R&R is super easy and accessible.  The removable resevoir is well designed and has yet to cause me any problems.  It can be removed and replaced into the coffemaker with no drips.  The unit rotates on the counter on its vertical axis on wheels under the base nicely for setup and filling.  One observation though - the coffemaker is 14\" high and your kitchen cupboards are probably 18\" above the counters, and the steam from the coffemaker comes out a small vent in the top center of the unit at fairly high velocity.  It is a good idea to pull it out from under the cabinets when in operation (which I do) so condensation doesn\'t wet down the underside of the cabinet.  But this is inconsequential to me. Timer and settings are great, nice blue LED readout on the front, looks great on the counter.  This costs a little more that some but you will not regret buying this coffeemaker. Oh yeah, guess what ? - it makes great coffee!!'),
(7273, 7, 3, 4, '2016-02-24', 'very good brewer, coffee is very hot, I like this size very good for work or garage would recommend , and the shipping was very fast and right to the door with no hassle'),
(7274, 7, 3, 3, '2015-01-26', 'This serves the purpose in my office for making one cup at a time. Needs to be refilled after every brew. Does not take the newer pods'),
(7275, 3, 1, 3, '2015-09-10', 'Works great, but gets HOOOT! Cooks and works great. Pretty easy to use and looks nice in our kitchen. But casing gets VERY HOT when using, doesn\'t seem safe. Definitely don\'t have it too close to anything when using it. I think that\'s a common problem with cheaper toaster ovens though. Usually cooks things much faster than directions call for, especially when using the convection feature.'),
(7276, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-18', '******* My toaster oven works perfectly, and it was delivered on time. It toast the bread evenly. Very excellent appliance to have in your kitchen.'),
(7277, 6, 1, 5, '2014-02-03', 'no issues I have used my toaster a couple of times since receiving it and it has worked great each time. My toast is toasted perfectly, i have no issue with the knobs. I am happy with my purchase.'),
(7278, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-30', 'Good, functional appliance Nice unit. A little hard to monitor toast, though.'),
(7279, 9, 1, 2, '2016-09-10', 'Great concept. Poor execution Great concept. Poor execution Was looking for something like this for a while. The big thing for me is a nice hot cup of coffee. While the brew is fine and the coffee tastes good. The temperature was sorely lacking. Not hot at all. Warm at best and no where near the four hours advertised.'),
(7280, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Easyyyy Peasyyyy Love the Kuerig! Copped one for my lady and I as a replacement for waiting in long drive thru\'s at local coffee shops. The water tank holds about 6 cups which lasts us throughout the day. Quick and easy, my type of coffee. The only struggle I had was figuring out how to fit the pod in the machine. It\'s much simpler than I thought. Just set the pod right in lol.  Kuerig has enlightened the mornings and put more cash in my pocket. Thanks, Kuerig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7281, 4, 1, 5, '2016-10-07', 'this the worst oven I have ever owned this the worst oven I have ever owned, I had a Black and Decker toaster oven for $20.00 that worked better than this one.Itwill not brown a biscuit ,it will burn toast  and doesn\'t broil very well .Basically just a bad toaster oven.It cost around $75.00 save your money.'),
(7282, 7, 3, 1, '2015-01-17', 'Very simple to use. Brews a terrific cup of coffee. Very reasonable price. I don\'t know what more you could ask of a K cup coffee maker. Highly recommend.'),
(7283, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-25', 'Safe and easy to use Does what it is supposed to do but made me very pleased with this item is that it is very easy and safe to use in comparison to the previous ones I tried.'),
(7284, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-20', 'Five Stars Just what I needed!'),
(7285, 7, 3, 1, '2016-07-02', 'Stopped working after 2 weeks. Received as a gift, so not terribly frustrated. Just shows how much the gift giver really cares. :-)'),
(7286, 12, 1, 5, '2015-02-02', 'I like the two appliances in one concept I like the two appliances in one concept. I use it to reheat left overs and works grest. What you reheat has to be pretty flat or no more than about two inches tall, but it\'s just what I need. The toaster fits bagels, which is a plus. Very easy to clean.'),
(7287, 3, 1, 4, '2014-12-30', 'Four Stars Just wish the LCD was backlit.'),
(7288, 8, 1, 4, '2014-07-04', 'It\'s just what I needed to make a good cup of coffee It\'s just what I needed to make a good cup of coffee. It\'s not fancy but it gets the job done & that is what matters.'),
(7289, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-02', 'I love the sleek and modern design of this blender I love the sleek and modern design of this blender. it looks great on my zen-themed kitchen. it also has the right voltage. makes the best fruit juice in town.'),
(7290, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-10', 'We replaced a Kruig coffee make with this Hamilton Beach model because of the reasonable cost and because we can use pods of our choice rather than having to purchase special Kruig pods required by the newer Kruig models. This efficient unit has measured up to its promises. We are very pleased with our purchase!'),
(7291, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-29', 'Quick and easy Absolutely love my Keurig! It\'s so quick and easy! The flavors of coffee are amazing too! http://click.eprizemail.com/?ju=fe20127470640278701379&ls=fdc015717d63057f761d777762&m=feff1072746d04&l=fe5417777d67067e7d1d&s=fe2e10767766067a771775&jb=ffcf14&t='),
(7292, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-27', 'Perfect for simple needs. I use this toaster every morning since March 27th. The side of the toast toward the middle of the toaster comes out a little darker than the other side, but both faces of the bread are toasted pretty evenly (just not quite equally). With the dial at \"4\", it comes out, every time, just about perfect for me. I haven\'t tried the other \"modes\" enough to rate them.'),
(7293, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', 'We have really enjoyed the Keurig K250 We have really enjoyed the Keurig K250.  We have loved being able to brew fresh coffee in a very short time. We love the convenience of not having coffee grounds to deal with and having our own preferences as to which type of coffee to brew each day.The removable water container is also a plus, as it\'s easy to fill at the sink.  We love our Keurig! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7294, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-22', 'Five Stars Perfect & so easy to use'),
(7295, 4, 1, 1, '2016-04-17', 'Glass door shattered while cooking. This oven literally cannot ... Glass door shattered while cooking. This oven literally cannot handle the heat. Used this thing approximately 5 times. Save your money and look elsewhere.'),
(7296, 1, 1, 2, '2015-10-22', 'Wish I could return ;( REALLY disappointed. I bought the 2.0 Brewing System assuming it was the most modern and best of the bunch. Unfortunately, it is not compatible with many of the k-cups in the market and on Amazon. About half of my \"variety packs\" gave me an error message which is nonsense. In fact, one of the offending pods actually worked but none of the identical varieties in the sample pack could register in the machine. I feel like it is deliberately temperamental to drive brand-name only purchases. Also, the pretty Sandy Pearl pictured here looks nothing like this in person and is probably the most boring beige imaginable. i really wish I could return this machine and get a version other than 2.0 in a better color but sadly I opened and used it not knowing it would refuse to work with most pods.'),
(7297, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-09', 'Five Stars It does it all, no need for large kitchen oven anymore. Toasts, bakes,  handles most any size task.'),
(7298, 4, 1, 5, '2015-01-11', 'Great for the price It\'s a second one I purchased in 3 years. The last one I got for my mother-in-law and we are all happy with it'),
(7299, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-21', 'Perfect size. Convenient and simple Perfect size. Convenient and simple. Make sure you don\'t overfill it with too much frozen stuff or the blades will come right out of the bottom! My bad!'),
(7300, 11, 1, 3, '2014-03-19', 'Door and timer not ideal I ordered this after reading the reviews. I wish I would have seen it in person. When you open the door, it does not slide out the wire rack at all. So, you have to reach inside the hot toaster to retrieve your items. The rack isn\'t attached to the door at all. The timer makes noise while the toaster is on the toast function. It ticks like a clock the whole time. My last B&D toaster did not do that, and it\'s just more of a nuisance than a problem. Good price.'),
(7301, 5, 1, 3, '2017-01-21', 'Was good while it lasted Was good while it lasted.  Bought this May 2015 and started gurgling and not brewing the last 2 cups of coffee.  Tried running white vinegar through to unclog it, but it is still clogged.  Loved that the water reservoir came off to fill.  Going to try the top rated Cuisinart.'),
(7302, 4, 1, 5, '2016-05-12', 'Great Counter Top Oven Best counter top unit I have ever had.  Like the newer model better that has just a toast timer and a constant on rather than this one\'s 30 Min. timer.  I generally cook small quantities so don\'t need the longer timer.'),
(7303, 10, 1, 5, '2015-03-27', 'Good blender-goos price. Great price and good blender. Blades are safely placed so you don\'t cut yourself when cleaning. Some blender blades are dangerously located with no protection when cleaning. Not a heavy-duty blender- not meant for crushing ice-cubes etc.'),
(7304, 1, 1, 5, '2016-02-05', 'Worked great So many poor reviews on this, i was scared to buy it. but, ive always wanted one. Im not a crazy coffee drinker, but i do like to occasionally have a hot beverage. I have not had this product long, i just received it yesterday. I purchased the violet one and its so cute. The power button to turn it off DOES work, you hold your finger on it for like 2 seconds and it turns off. I am still waiting to get my pods from the Keurig website, so i almost waited to set up my machine, but when i opened it up, i discovered that there were samples in there!! 3 coffee pods, 1 hot cocoa pod, and 3 iced tea pods! It also comes with filters and cleaners etc. I wasnt expecting all that, so it was a nice surprise. The water container DOES come off, which makes it easy to take to the sink, i just dont like how the lid doesnt latch on it. I live in high altitude, 7000 feet, and this supposedly only works up to 6000 feet, but there is a high altitude function which is awesome. I havent checked to see if i have to set that function on every time i turn the keurig on, ill have to check that out when i get home. I followed the directions perfectly. ran hot water through it first, then put a hot cocoa pod in. There is a checkbox to select hot cocoa pod. It brewed HOT, my tongue is mad at me. it tasted delicious, not watery. after i brewed the cocoa, it says to run hot water through it again to clear the cocoa out, so i did. Everything was easy. i cant wait to get all my other pods from Keurig. I ordered some really fun ones!'),
(7305, 12, 1, 5, '2016-06-16', 'Five Stars great thank you'),
(7306, 6, 1, 3, '2015-04-14', 'Budget choice with only minor drawbacks Nice basic toaster with simple operation. Bagel slices are a tight fit and need an extra push down the tray -- a tiny inconvenience. Heating is not even but is adequate for a college or graduate student like yours truly.'),
(7307, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-01', 'Love this toaster oven Love this toaster oven! Perfect for cooking something in a pinch! Since I am single, it is nice not to always start up the full sized oven.  Great for cooking pizzas, warming up leftovers or just toasting bread. I usually try to keep my cabinets fee of appliances, but this is definitely an exception.'),
(7308, 3, 1, 5, '2015-02-08', 'best one ever I love this, never had one that was this awesome'),
(7309, 11, 1, 5, '2015-10-29', 'Love this durable toaster oven! I\'ve had this toaster oven for almost a year now and I LOVE it! I\'ve done away with my regular toaster and use it every day for toast in the morning. I also use it to cook small batches of things like fish in aluminum foil, or baked brie. Of course, it\'s great for things like pizza bagels, etc. It\'s a great value for the price!'),
(7310, 11, 1, 4, '2014-12-21', 'Nice little toaster I bought this last year for my mom for Christmas since she wanted a toaster oven. It still works great. No complaints about it and my mom is super picky. It\'s not big at all which is great if u have small space like we do. But it\'s not too small. Me and my boyfriend use it at the same time to toast sandwiches and its fine. I recommend this toaster.'),
(7311, 3, 1, 5, '2014-12-21', 'This toaster oven does a good job. It is quite in convection mode and ... This toaster oven does a good job.  It is quite in convection mode and easy to use. It does get warm / hot on top and sides, but it is a toaster oven and they do that. Have been using it more now than the larger oven.'),
(7312, 5, 1, 1, '2014-03-21', 'Stopped working immediately after the 1 month return window. Worked great for 36 days, then in the middle of a pot it no longer takes in water from the tank.  Not very reliable.  Lesson learned I guess, never buy a used coffee maker.'),
(7313, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-04', 'Five Stars I love the removable water container.'),
(7314, 7, 3, 1, '2015-07-08', 'i had this coffee maker for i would say month worked fine until i cleaned it i did exactly what it said to do . now it wont brew .wont get hot , wont even dispense water just stays on super frustrated . never again will i get this product and not all k-cups work in this coffee maker'),
(7315, 10, 1, 1, '2015-11-21', 'One Star I don\'t know why, but it doesn\'t work!!! It just makes big noises and doesn\'t work!!!!!'),
(7316, 10, 1, 1, '2015-05-25', 'One Star this s*** doesn\'t work'),
(7317, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-01', 'If it weren\'t all black... Wonderful coffee maker.  If I would suggest one thing to make it more useful, it would be to make the inner area where the pot goes, not black, but a lighter color, like white or gray, etc.  As another reviewer commented, it is pretty difficult to see how much coffee is in the pot, and sometimes it is really impossible.  So, if you don\'t take the time to check out the pot, it is easy to just pour water from a bottle into the tank and press start or put it on automatic...only to find out that there was old coffee still left in the pot.  Well, after you do that a couple of times...yes, you learn to look.  Every time I finally find something that works well, when I need a replacement, it seems that the model is either discontinued or re-designed.  So, I bought two.  Now I have a spare.'),
(7318, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-08', 'We have been happy. It toasts just fine This toastation was replacing our traditional two slice toaster that finally died.  I wanted a toaster oven but did not want to have to make room for another appliance.  We decided to give this a try even with some negative reviews.  We have been happy.  It toasts just fine; my breads are homemade and thick.  My oldest son was here for 3 weeks and used the toaster oven part daily.  He had no complaints of it not warming appropriately and was happy with how it functions, easy.  He was only heating things up, which is what I purchased it to do.  We have not tried to \"bake\" anything small it, but I do not plan on ever using it for that.  I would recommend this to others.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(7319, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-03', 'So far, so good I\'ve been using this model for a year now and am quite satisfied. I love the convex glass making it much more functional. I\'ve had many toaster ovens over the past 40 years and have come to expect a certain lifespan. I do see that with this oven the upper heating element has been redesigned and your less likely to hit it and cause it to be useless. But so far, so good.'),
(7320, 6, 1, 4, '2017-01-06', 'Good toaster, quick and does a good Good toaster,quick and does a good job.'),
(7321, 5, 1, 4, '2014-03-22', 'Well I wonder? The coffeemaker works fine.I\'m just not sure about the water reservoir.You have to pull it out just so.If your a little off then it\'s tough to remove and I\'m betting it\'s hard on it.I don\'t see this lasting that long.That\'s only a guess on my part and so far no problems.If I do have any I will update this review.'),
(7322, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'Nice little coffee maker Great coffee maker.It was a little smaller than I thought but overall I am happy with it.'),
(7323, 11, 1, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Great little toaster oven I love this little toaster oven. Have been using it every day (often 2-3 times a day) for a year. And it works great.'),
(7324, 1, 1, 4, '2016-03-29', 'Which model is best? There are so many models, I\'m not sure I obtained the one I wanted.  But, makes coffee fine.'),
(7325, 6, 1, 4, '2015-09-27', 'Four Stars I LIKE IT--I USE IT DAILY FOR TOAST OR ENGLISH MUFINS'),
(7326, 8, 1, 3, '2016-10-15', 'The material feels cheap but it gives you a cup ... The material feels cheap but it gives you a cup of coffee and I can\'t really complain considering how cheap it is.'),
(7327, 2, 1, 1, '2016-08-15', 'Poorly made, unsafe, fire hazard. If you enjoy nearly burning down your house, this toaster oven is for you. Granted, I could\'ve just received a lemon from the seller/company, I still feel obligated to write an honest review. When in use, there are vents on the side of the oven on side opposite of the knobs. There must have been shotty wiring or something come loose because when I turned it on to toast a bagel, I left for about 1 minute. Came back to my kitchen to find it looking like a Snoop Dogg concert. The smoke alarm was going off and my bagel was still untoasted. I checked the trays, top and bottom there was nothing in the oven that\'d make it smoke up like that. It was coming from the unit itself. Just my luck, took me over a month to unbox the thing I\'ve been so busy with work for the past month. The Amazon warranty is now up as well unfortunately. Going to follow up with the manufacturer to see if they\'ll back up their product. It\'s a lot of work for toasted bagels. Had a $12 toaster from target work better than this. Be careful and watch your unit closely if you decide to purchase.'),
(7328, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-28', 'Five Stars Love this toaster!!!'),
(7329, 3, 1, 4, '2015-07-15', 'great appliance I have only had it a short time but have use all its functions and it has performed flawlessly'),
(7330, 4, 1, 1, '2016-05-31', 'It was ok until it wasn\'t. HAZARD.. ... It was ok until it wasn\'t.  HAZARD...SHATTERING GLASS   My daughter made toast and we had just sat down to chat when we heard a shattering noise. The glass  on the front door completely shattered taking away part of the door\'s metal frame.  Luckily we were not standing there.  I know there are more reports of cracked heating elements but this is not an isolated case and should be investigated. BUYER BEWARE'),
(7331, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-14', 'One Star never worked'),
(7332, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-14', 'Great for single servings and shelf space It\'s plastic, single-speed, and the blade is non-removable, but it\'s perfect for mixing up a serving of Soylent with a banana and some chocolate syrup.'),
(7333, 3, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Black & Decker good name this is my second one the other was smaller. Love my new oven. Since I live alone really beats heating up house with using my regular oven. When my son saw he also ordered one for himself.'),
(7334, 6, 1, 3, '2014-09-10', 'Three Stars Only toasts on one side.'),
(7335, 4, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'The oven is nicely build. Only wish that it is bigger to ... The oven is nicely build. Only wish that it is bigger to fit 6-slice of bread, The temperature is high enough to get the cooking right.'),
(7336, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-29', 'Great product Works great!'),
(7337, 12, 1, 3, '2015-09-09', 'Too small I wanted to love this, but Returned this because it is so tiny. If you only need the size of two bread slices (and nothing very tall), this will work for you. But I like to put in bowls to reheat, and none will fit in here, just the little tray it comes with.'),
(7338, 9, 1, 4, '2015-02-11', 'Must wipe valve inside coffee maker with vinegar once or twice a month to ensure drip/leak free operation. I purchased mine from Bed Bath etc.. in April 2014. Reviewing today on Feb 11, 2015 because of a drip. The bottom of the tank has a reminder to open the valve while rinsing to avoid drips -- makes sense. Coffee build up or the occasional ground from a collapsed filter (I confess I prefer paper filters) can get built up in there. I religiously rinse that valve, but a couple of months ago the coffee maker on one morning simply poured brewed coffee out of the release valve, filled up the catcher tray, and covered my counter. Of course I then cleaned everything up and wiped out the inside of the tank and rinsed that valve in the tank repeatedly. However, the coffee maker still leaks occasionally so now, I never brew coffee without a coffee cup under the valve. This morning the cup was half full of coffee. I finally called Cuisinart in desperation. They established the tank was not leaking by having me fill it and hold it over the sink. Then the service rep asked me to take a paper towel with vinegar on it and wipe around and under the valve on the inside of the coffee maker. This is the valve on the other end of the flapper that releases hot coffee and turns on the light. The towel did come away with coffee residue and after a couple of wipes, I even asked  the service rep if I should do that with a Q tip (it\'s a tight fit). He said a paper towel with vinegar was sufficient, also confirming that pouring vinegar into the inside of the coffee maker without the tank present IS NOT RECOMMENDED.  Wiping  around and under the valve fixed the issue for now.  Recommended interval for this cleaning with vinegar? About once or twice a month.  I made an annotation in my manual to remind me. I would buy this coffee maker again even with this extra maintenance requirement because I love love love the carafe free operation. Cuisinart should probably revise its manual though.'),
(7339, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-27', 'Keurig great machine We recently purchased a 2.0 Keurig as a wedding present for ourselves some thing we always wanted. It is simply amazing.  We don\'t drink coffee but love hot tea, hot chocolate, cider and lemonade.  Like having the option for coffee with guests.  Thanks for the great system. Love it. We look forward to trying new products in the Keurig.'),
(7340, 12, 1, 4, '2017-01-05', 'i like this oven toaster although you have to watch when ... i like this oven toaster although you have to watch when baking. the element is very close to the food!.'),
(7341, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-29', 'i love this coffeepot you will be amazed with the coffee ... i love this coffeepot you will be amazed with the coffee it makes i had to replace a mr coffee pot that i had for 8 years and i would recomend this one'),
(7342, 12, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', '... have to turn the oven on for small items like a piece of salmon I purchased this for my bungalow so I do not have to turn the oven on for small items like a piece of salmon, garlic bread.  I love the toaster , it toasts so quickly!  You can close the toast area so it can keep anything from falling in like dust or what not!  Most people will use a toaster cover--who wants that?!!!'),
(7343, 3, 1, 2, '2015-03-08', 'The toaster function is slow. The item itself is ... The toaster function is slow. The item itself is huge and takes up tons of counter space. People actually comment when they visit that the appliance is too large'),
(7344, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-11', 'Everything I was hoping for This is my first coffee maker and I\'m incredibly pleased with it. Great function and look, all in one package. The carafe feels a little on the cheap side, but I\'ve not had any problems with it. My favorite feature has to be the timer. You make all the preparations the night before, turn the \"program\" button on, then wake up to your morning coffee being ready. It\'s also great that it has a \"keep warm\" feature that will keep the coffee warm (through a high, medium, or low setting), so that if you sleep in or otherwise miss the timer it will keep it warm in the carafe up to 2 hours before the auto-shut off (I believe). Would recommend!'),
(7345, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-10', 'Five Stars love it'),
(7346, 9, 1, 3, '2017-01-13', 'well it worked alright for the money, but the ... well it worked alright for the money, but the warranty is 3 years, and it died (water leaking everywhere) at 3 years and 3 weeks.'),
(7347, 2, 1, 4, '2015-02-15', 'This product is good for what I use it for I had to replace a similar toaster oven that was at the end of it\'s life.  This product is good for what I use it for: toasting bread/bagels, heating pizza, and making Eggo Waffles.  The only complaints are: it\'s a little tricky to get the toast settings at the correct levels (I like lightly toasted, but it\'s hard to get it just right so I often get it overtoasted to my tastes) and if you use the drip tray for something like pizza, the bottom of the pizza never gets crunchy the way I like it.'),
(7348, 12, 1, 5, '2016-11-07', 'Works like a dream Works like a dream! Perfect for one slice on pizza in the toaster oven and makes longer cliched bread toast perfectly!.'),
(7349, 3, 1, 2, '2014-08-10', 'let me update this negative review I have used this for about three weeks and although it does work, the text on the buttons if very hard to read, the timer bell rings once and is barely audible, and the widow with the temperature and timer fogs so that you can\'t read it.  there is not interior light so you have to open the door to check what\'s cooking.  The indicators as to what is on are so small that you can\'t really see them.  The exterior of the oven, while cooking and after, becomes much too hot to touch, so much so that a serious burn is inevitable.  90 bucks or so, you get what you pay for. So, I found out that Black and Decker is owned by Spectrum Brands and they actually responded.  I accepted their invitation to contact them about the issues I am having with this oven and, much to my surprise, am actually pleased with the results.  I am completely satisfied with the resolution.  I still  have the oven, it still has issues, and I still rate it two stars.  But, based on my experience, I rate Spectrum Brands FIVE stars.  Visit their website, http://www.spectrumbrands.com, and find out how many other brands they own.  If this one example is typical of their desire to satisfy their customers, it will be worth seeking out and purchasing products that they own.  Shame all companies aren\'t more like Spectrum.'),
(7350, 10, 1, 4, '2015-06-10', 'Four Stars Good with fruits.  Maybe not with veges.'),
(7351, 6, 1, 2, '2016-03-15', 'Two Stars This toaster off-gassed a strong plastic smell while in use.  I exchanged it for a stainless steel toaster.'),
(7352, 4, 1, 5, '2015-11-28', 'Beyond Happy Customer! We are over the moon happy with this item! It all started when our microwave quit and we went 2 months without anything but our stove. Then we started researching about the possible dangers of microwaves and purchased this instead. Seriously, once you warm something up in this you will NEVER want to use a microwave again! Pizza heated up in this gets crispy and not soggy like the microwave. We heated chicken alfredo take out up and it got slightly browned and delicious! We are so happy with this purchase! I\'m not sure what people are talking about it not having a timer, we put bagels and toast in it and you set it on light medium or dark and the buzzer goes off and shuts off.'),
(7353, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-29', '... this for a few days but man is it awesome. I\'m a big tea person Only had this for a few days but man is it awesome. I\'m a big tea person, so I\'ve been brewing a lot of tea. So far, I\'ve had no issue using k-cups, the refillable keurig.com brand k-cup, and a refillable k-carafe off brand with no issue. The tank is definitely on the small side, but the 12 cup coffeemaker I previously had was total overkill for a household of 2. Also, this thing comes with a filter and the descaling solution, so you don\'t have to buy those right away.'),
(7354, 7, 3, 1, '2015-10-03', 'Had my machine for about a month then it just stopped working.. I emptied it completely and started again still doesn\'t work..In the garbage it goes.'),
(7355, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-17', 'Five Stars So far it has been working great, but I have not had it that long.'),
(7356, 9, 1, 2, '2015-01-26', 'Two Stars The plastic coffee tub has a metal warmer touching the coffee. I didn\'t care for the flavor when brewed'),
(7357, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-06', 'I wouldn\'t need anything more.  Highly recommend. This things is awesome.  I wanted a high quality toaster and toaster oven, but I wanted to save on counter space. Guess what?  I bought this and haven\'t looked back since.'),
(7358, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-30', '... had for for several days now and I\'m totally pleased with it I\'ve had for for several days now and I\'m totally pleased with it.  It\'s sturdy and good looking.  I wanted a coffee maker that I could fill without opening the top to pour in water.  Like most people my wall cabinets make it hard to get to the top of a coffee maker comfortably.  This unit has a removable water reservoir in the back.  The unit turns on wheels to let you get to the reservoir easily.  I love this feature.  It\'s easy to get the reservoir off and on and it doesn\'t leak. The unit has several settings for how warm you\'d like to keep the coffee. There\'s even a setting for bold brewing.  That feature lets me brew with less ground coffee in the basket.  I like the slim space saving profile, too.  I would recommend this unit to anyone.'),
(7359, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-26', 'excellent toast It has worked flawlessly... great. .....'),
(7360, 7, 3, 5, '2016-06-04', 'I\'ve been through three Keurigs, one Mr. Coffee k-brewer and a scoop brewer by Hamilton Beach. This one by far makes better coffee, and I like that I can choose regular or bold. You can use ground coffee or k-cups or pods.... nice to have a choice! For the price and function of this machine, I\'ll never waste money on another expensive Keurig, that I know will break within a year!'),
