(7386, 1, 1, 4, '2015-07-01', 'The only thing I don\'t like about it is that you need to manually turn ... I just upgraded from the mini that I have been using for the past 4 years. The main reason being I wanted to have a machine that stored the water vs having to fill it every time. The only thing I don\'t like about it is that you need to manually turn it off unless you want it to have hot water all of the time. Additionally, it is not readily apparent HOW to turn it off. I had to call Keurig to find out! Other than that I really love it. I think the beverages are more uniform as you select what size and how strong you want them to be. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
