(7434, 2, 1, 4, '2016-06-12', 'Four Stars Very nice product.'),
(7435, 2, 1, 5, '2015-05-06', 'Great toaster oven I REPLACED A MUCH BIGGER AND MORE EXPENSIVE COVECTION OVEN/TOASTER MACHINE, WITH WHICH I WAS NOT PARTICULARLY HAPPY, WITH THIS BLACK & DECKER TOASTER OVEN. I LOVE THIS LITTLE NUMBER- IT DOES ALL IT IS SUPOSSED TO WELL AND EFFICIENTLY. I WOULD BUY IT AGAIN.'),
(7436, 3, 1, 4, '2015-03-29', 'my bad I should of looked at the dimensions before I ... I bought this for my Mum, her toaster had broken and I thought she\'d get more use from a toaster oven. Her only complaint was the size, it\'s HUGE , my bad I should of looked at the dimensions before I had it shipped to her. She likes it but she said it takes up a lot of space on her counter.'),
(7437, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-21', 'minor irratation works fine, but not sure why, on broil, when setting the temp dial, that function is the second from the last \"notch\" in stead of the last one.  seems like a no brainer.  sometimes it results in the broiler not operating as hot as it should if we forget to make the correct setting.'),
(7438, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-23', 'Pretty good oven I like this oven. The controls are a little confusing, but it cooks efficiently and evenly and I am pleased.'),
(7439, 6, 1, 4, '2015-05-10', 'Nice Little Toaster I really like this little toaster. After suffering through several toaster ovens, we got this little beauty. The only con I can think of is that the dial for setting how much you want your bread toasted is kind of loose and feels a little flimsy. Other than that, I haven\'t had a single problem with it.'),
(7440, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-30', 'Love it! Quick shipping and works great. My bother has one so I decided to get one for myself. Since it is basically a mini blender it isn\'t as powerful as the big ones, but its great for college students. I use it to make fruit drinks and I love how I can make it then grab and go! And the price is fantastic!'),
(7441, 5, 1, 4, '2016-02-07', 'Broken Panel but Still Works I ordered one for my family a year and a half ago and it still works great. My relatives wanted one as well so I ordered this for them. When it arrived, the plate covering the buttons and the display is broken off. It appears to still work fine though so I won\'t return it. But, ... to be honest with you, I just don\'t feel like shipping it back. There are probably much better coffee machines at a similar price but I know this one works fine and it is reliable so I won\'t risk getting another brand. Next time, I\'ll do the research and look for a different brand.'),
(7442, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-07', 'Good Gift item Purchased as a gift and it seems to be working just fine! Looks Good and Cooks Good I might get one for myself.'),
(7443, 5, 1, 5, '2016-08-13', 'Nice coffee pot! Very easy to use. Sleek design Love the bold coffee option.'),
(7444, 6, 1, 5, '2015-04-01', 'Five Stars Works so well so far!'),
(7445, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-22', 'good Beautiful stainless steel look adds to any counter top. Preprogrammed settings make roasting and baking many common items a breeze'),
(7446, 10, 1, 1, '2015-01-13', 'Waste of money Only buy this is you like returning items. Don\'t dream of using ice in this. Only good if you blend very soft fruits or very soft vegetables. That\'s how pointless this product is. Another Hamilton Beach disappointment.....'),
(7447, 10, 1, 4, '2015-04-07', 'Four Stars Works much better than expected!'),
(7448, 7, 3, 2, '2016-09-25', 'Agree with Coffeelover\'s review; can\'t make a strong cup of coffee. First used one cup of water, two tablespoons of coffee...way too weak. Tried using a heaping measure of coffee (roughly 2.5 tbs coffee) and 3/4 cup water, but then ended up with just over half-a-mug of coffee and honestly it wasn\'t great. I didn\'t try 3 tbs because the instructions indicate that overloading the basket will cause coffee to overflow. No idea how you would brew a travel mug-full. Also, to insert the K-cups, or to use the filter for grounds, there\'s the extra step of first removing the holder, placing the K-cup or basket in it, and then inserting into the unit. Not a lot, but not as convenient as my current K cup brewer or even plain old drip unit. Just didn\'t impress me (and I wanted to be impressed!).'),
(7449, 4, 1, 1, '2016-01-02', 'Bottom element is the culprit like everyone elses Failed in less than 2 years. Bottom element is the culprit like everyone elses. Cuisinart is no longer welcome in my kitchen.'),
(7450, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-13', 'Five Stars My wife calls it the crack toaster.  It gets hot fast!'),
(7451, 4, 1, 4, '2015-04-28', 'Works fine This oven toaster toasts much faster than any we\'ve ever owned. Wish there was a way to adjust the volume or decrease the number of beeps. Still, far better than others we\'ve used and worth the purchase.'),
(7452, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-11', 'Great! Great! Compact, can drink from the cup. Definitely good for making shakes and getting to work.'),
(7453, 6, 1, 4, '2014-11-12', 'Great Toaster! This toaster is a quality product. We are well satisfied with item.   Kenneth Willson'),
(7454, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-17', 'works wonderful after 4 months of use works wonderful after 4 months of use...beep is just little too loud, but overall it is a good product.'),
(7455, 10, 1, 4, '2015-03-24', 'The fruit must be destroyed. I hate bananas. I hate strawberries. I hate blueberries. I hate pineapple. I want to destroy all fruit. This personal blender enables me to slowly achieve my ultimate goal  a world without fruit. It easily tears through all the fruits I throw into it and does so in a quick manner. I can pulse it and make their destruction slower while I laugh at their screams or I can hold it and watch them get torn apart as I smile while they die. I can drown them in juice and water while cutting them up with this or even add powders such as protein or pre-workout and this blender will evenly distribute those items amongst the evil fruit. The best part is that the remains of the fruit are delicious and creamy. Ill continue to destroy these fruits using this personal blender until smoothies grow on trees. The second best part is that its a personal size. A full blender is probably two servings, but I water it down enough to make it only one. Forget those bullet blenders  theyre terrible. Get this for half the price and double the power. And destroy all fruit.'),
(7456, 4, 1, 5, '2016-04-04', 'Five Stars Love it!'),
(7457, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-28', 'Highly recommend I love this blender. Makes perfect portion sizes. This also chops ice. I highly recommend this blender.'),
(7458, 8, 1, 4, '2016-04-03', 'Id buy again Suits my needs. Small coffee pot. Fills up two mugs of coffee and very easy to clean'),
(7459, 2, 1, 3, '2015-11-06', 'Poor vision I have found it very hard to read the knobs to change settings . Wish I had noticed this in the ad..'),
(7460, 7, 3, 1, '2016-09-23', 'We purchased the 1st one about 6 months ago, and it started just not making a full cup of coffee. It would spit and sputter, but never complete. The blue light would continue to blink. We purchased a second, and within a week; it started doing the same thing. Don\'t buy this coffee pot!'),
(7461, 12, 1, 4, '2014-08-26', 'As small as it probably seems No real issues so far, but there have been a couple things that wouldn\'t fit.'),
(7462, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-15', 'so good. The oven tray is a little tight for a bagel, but so far, so good.'),
(7463, 5, 1, 5, '2016-09-07', 'love it love it.'),
(7464, 8, 1, 2, '2016-07-29', 'I dont recommend this coffeemaker I dont recommend this coffeemaker. Although it works fine for the price, it has an awful plastic smell that carries over to the brewed coffee making it taste terrible. I use this coffeemaker daily and  Ive washed the whole machine several times and it still has same smell even after 2 months. Awful!.'),
(7465, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-09', 'Great oroduct Love this coffee maker. Easy to read display. The crafe doesn\'t spill a drop when pouring. Easy to fill, detachable water reservoir.'),
(7466, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-08', 'Hooray for toast! Toast looks good, hooray!.'),
(7467, 3, 1, 4, '2016-04-27', 'Good oven Nice counter oven. Its just hard to see the controls. Only thing i dont like about it. Beside that it does the job.'),
(7468, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-06', 'Great coffee maker! This system is so much easier to use and makes great coffee when combined with a burr grinder. Worth every penny!'),
(7469, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-25', 'Five Stars Makes a great cup of coffee. Can\'t beat the value.'),
(7470, 4, 1, 1, '2016-04-17', 'WARNING:  FIRE HAZARD DUE TO CRACKED HEATING ELEMENT How is it that Cuisinart can continue to sell this item when there have been so many reports of cracked heating elements and even fires?  I purchased this toaster oven several years ago and have recently noticed that the lower element has a crack in it. The cracked area glows brighter than the rest of the element.  I have no idea how long the crack has been there -- but not taking any chances.  This is a fire waiting to happen.  Even though the item works fine and I like the design overall, it\'s going in the trash and I will be looking to purchase a different brand.'),
(7471, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-16', 'It\'s great to make 12 cups worth and it last me ... This one went to my daughters house.  I have an older model at my house and needed this at hers.  It\'s great to make 12 cups worth and it last me two to three days.  Take out the coffee grounds and Ur good to go after you put it in a container for the next days  Love this style.  One cup ate time for however many people'),
(7472, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-26', 'Love not having a pot Everything I expected. Love not having a pot. Just the coffee maker!.'),
(7473, 8, 1, 4, '2016-01-24', 'Functional Coffee Pot Nothing special but gets the job done.'),
(7474, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-29', 'Recommend Perfect'),
(7475, 9, 1, 5, '2015-01-04', 'I love this coffeemaker I bought this coffeemaker 6 months ago and waited until now to submit a review. I wanted to be sure I would either love it or hate. I LOVE it still. The most important feature is the lack of a carafe. I had been looking for just this type of coffeemaker without having to pay over $400 so I was pretty pleased when I saw this one, but the bad reviews really made me consider it quite seriously. I have had absolutely no problems. The coffee stays hot but doesn\'t scorch. It turns itself off automatically but we always finish the pot before the time limit. It is very easy to clean. The gauge, while not the most accurate, provides a general indication of amount left. I use both the gold filter provided and insert a paper filter within. That way I don\'t get any stray grounds leaking through the gold filter. Works like a charm. And I like the 1-4 cup feature. I have not needed to use the timer so I can\'t report on that feature. The ONLY negative I have to report is that it really doesn\'t brew 12 cups efficiently. The grounds puff up so much they run over the gold filter and make a mess. When we want to brew for several guests we brew 8 cups and serve, then brew the next batch. Or if we have decaf drinkers we use a second pot. So if you are still on the fence like I was for a while, give this coffeemaker a try. The price Amazon is listing right now can\'t be beat. I paid a lot more at a retail outlet on sale.'),
(7476, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-02', 'Five Stars Excellent quality.'),
(7477, 2, 1, 3, '2015-05-13', 'Three Stars Smaller than what I expected.'),
(7478, 12, 1, 1, '2016-01-28', 'Oven is useless There is no timer and the oven is useless.'),
(7479, 9, 1, 4, '2015-09-20', 'Not quite what I expected. I\'ve had this less than a week but I find it to be just ok.  It is larger than expected (replaced a Hamilton Beach which was slightly smaller.). Coffee does stay hot longer, is easy to program, and as with most coffee makers it doesn\'t work for under-the-cabinet (i solved this by using an appliance caddy underneath, and it works great.). What I am most irritated by is the water tank.  On mine, at least, it does not slide into position easily.  If it is even 1/4 inch off, it will not work and you could be trying for awhile to figure out why.  With each passing day, though, it gets slighyly easier to put in place.  For that reason, I am only giving it a 4.'),
(7480, 1, 1, 5, '2015-11-04', 'I married my machine I purchased this two weeks ago and I love it oh so much! I\'m an avid 4 cups a day coffee drinker so this machine makes life so much easier for me. The set up is easy, the cleaning is quick and the coffee is hot and yummy~  *Note: Why are people comparing this machine to the mini? The mini makes one cup of coffee at a time with no water reservoir and it\'s small, meant for dorms. This is more of a family keurig. The comparisons are void. But anyways here is my list to you: Pros: -It\'s super quiet. My sister has the Keurig b60 and it\'s super loud when you turn it on, it\'s heating up and when it dispenses the coffee. This machine is beautiful if you have babies or grouchy old relatives. -It\'s fast! Takes maybe 40 seconds to heat up, 10 seconds to dispense coffee and 30 seconds in between usage to reheat the water for another cup of coffee. It\'s beautiful :\') It takes longer for my old kettle of water to heat up. -It\'s compact. It fits really nicely on my little kitchen counter top and it doesnt take up too much space or look crammed. I also put a k cup rotating holder next to it and it looks so high end hehe. -It\'s light weight. It\'s not heavy or bulky at all and it\'s easy to move around :) Cons: -The in between water preheating takes about 30 seconds which is not a big deal, but apparently some reviews dont have that kind of time? lol -If you have a travel mug/tumbler that is on the long side it will not fit under the coffee dispenser, even with the drip catcher removed. If you drink a lot of coffee in the morning about 16-32 oz I would recommend buying a short and fat travel mug that way it fits under the spout. (That\'s what I did) -It doesnt dispense a large quantity of coffee at once. So if you have a large cup/travel mug youre going to have to use the machine a couple of times. Ex: For a 16 oz mug youre going to need to use 2, 8 oz rotations. That results in 2 k cups or 1 k cup-but weak coffee. -It does not have auto shut off, which kind of does suck and to me this is the only actual con because as a college student I\'m very rushed in the mornings and so I buy things that shut off automatically( hair straightener, lamp, computer etc.), so when I noticed that this coffee maker does not shut off automatically I was a bit let down.... but not enough to give it 3 or 4 stars. :3 That\'s about it for this coffee maker, I could talk about how k cups are pretty pricey but that would be irrelevant because 1.) You can buy the reusable k cup that uses your own ground coffee and 2.) If you dont want to deal with the price of k cups then this machine is not for you. Overall I love this machine to death and it can be that I\'m still in the honeymoon stage but if we get in an argument I will update here soon and discuss my changed attitude. -Jenn'),
(7481, 3, 1, 5, '2016-06-22', 'Five Stars Great Product'),
(7482, 9, 1, 5, '2016-11-28', 'IMHO keurig is 2nd This is my second pot. Gave the first one to my son because I was gifted a keurig. After realizing how much coffee I was wasting, I decided to go back to my favorite. I love this pot.'),
(7483, 1, 1, 5, '2016-06-14', 'Five Stars Awesome!'),
(7484, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-15', 'Five Stars Nice and small, works great'),
(7485, 3, 1, 3, '2015-12-18', 'This is a bottom of the line toaster. All ... This is a bottom of the line toaster.  All the other reviews and complaints about it are correct.  Just know what youre buying before you do'),
(7486, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-17', 'Five Stars WONDERFUL for dorms.'),
(7487, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-06', 'good coffee maker. I like this coffee maker.  Brews well.  Can vary amount, and keeps warm.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(7488, 10, 1, 4, '2015-06-06', 'Makes great milkshakes, even when I add whole pecans Makes great milkshakes, even when I add whole pecans.  Make sure to slide the cover over the mouth piece before turning it on.  The switch is momentary (You can\'t turn it on and walk away.)  Takes very little counter space and cleans up easily.  For the price, this thing is great.'),
(7489, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-05', 'I really like taking the water tank to the sink for filling ... I really like taking the water tank to the sink for filling and that you can see the water level.'),
(7490, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-12', 'Cuisinart CPT-122 Toaster This is a fantastic toaster.  Cool to the touch except on the metal slots. I have found it to toast bread evenly on both sides, have not tried anything but bread. Nice bright white color and long cord.  I searched for just the right toaster for a long time and settled on this one.  I\'m glad I did!'),
(7491, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Bought this coffee maker not knowing how fancy it actually ... Bought this coffee maker not knowing how fancy it actually was.  I was very impressed with the quality of the maker and the different options of brewing style I could choose from. Also, I had a very pleasant experience with the customer support in helping me figure out some problems I had with the older version of the k-cups.  I will forever be a Keurig user! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(7492, 12, 1, 5, '2014-12-13', 'I love it. This is my second toastation toaster.  I love it.'),
(7493, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-21', 'Could not be happier with this Hamilton Beach Coffeemaker Could not be happier with this Hamilton Beach Coffeemaker!  The features it offers are thoughtful and better than any of the other coffeemakers we\'ve owned, including some very expensive ones.  Coffee does taste better and smells better while making for some reason, it really is a great coffeemaker.  It owns up to the description of features perfectly!'),
(7494, 2, 1, 3, '2016-10-31', 'Short plug: short cord Shortest cord ever: has to be plugged in at an odd angle. Otherwise, couldn\'t been a contender..'),
(7495, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-24', 'The Keurig K200! The perfect brewer for me. To put it simply, I love Keurig brewers. I\'m the owner of a previous generation Platinum brewer that I cared for like my fourth child. However, as much as I loved it, I really felt like it was time to upgrade to a newer brewer and go with something that had a much smaller footprint for my counter space. I have to say I have been VERY pleased. Sure you can\'t use pods from the previous generation, but there is certainly no shortage of variety with the 2.0 pods. I\'ve also seen a lot of negative reviews stating that you\'re forced into using Keurig 2.0 pods and that there isn\'t a My K-Cup type option. This is purely false. I found a My K-Cup option at my local Walmart for like $5 that\'s compatible with Keurig 1.0 & 2.0 brewers. I\'ve been using my own coffee from day one and have yet to be stuck with Keurig pods of any fashion. I purchased this brewer in red and absolutely love it. It has not disappointed me as of yet. The only reason I\'m giving a 4-star review is because there is no temperature adjustment on any of the 2.0 generation brewers, unlike the former Platinum brewer that I had. The 2.0 generation brews coffee at a steady 175 degrees, but the ideal temperature is somewhere between 192 and 205. On my previous brewer I could max the temp up to 192 degrees. Unfortunately, from what I have seen, you cannot adjust this on any of the latest generation, not even the higher end models. At any rate, I\'m very pleased with the purchase and performance of the machine and would certainly buy it again.'),
(7496, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-15', 'Good little toaster Works well, the outside stays cool and is compact enough to fit where I keep it, size does matter! I like that u can thaw frozen bread and reheat.  It has a lift so u can get smaller pieces of bread out.'),
(7497, 12, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Five Stars works great'),
(7498, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-09', 'great size for one or two people Sometimes you just don\'t need a huge pot. Sometimes you do though. Be aware there is no auto shut off.'),
(7499, 8, 1, 5, '2016-03-04', 'Five Stars Awesome'),
(7500, 11, 1, 5, '2014-10-06', 'Five Stars great item.'),
(7501, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-30', 'Five Stars It\'s a great coffee maker.  No problems.'),
(7502, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-22', 'It Doesn\'t Blend Anything Forget blending ice, this thing can\'t even blend yogurt and soft ice cream by itself. I read the entire manual to make sure I did in fact use it properly, and it does have a list of items it can\'t blend, but it can\'t even get the basics. I honestly did a better \"blending\" job mashing the yogurt with ice cream with a spoon and a cup.'),
(7503, 10, 1, 1, '2015-09-19', 'cheap, spend more to get quality Broke four days after using it. The power simply stopped working.'),
(7504, 12, 1, 3, '2016-09-30', 'I like the style and functionality of this toaster I like the style and functionality of this toaster.  I have used it for about six weeks but am disappointed with the basic toasting feature.  It\'s not consistent, some parts are nicely toasted, others not at all and some burnt.  Also the toaster oven is small and narrow.'),
(7505, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-21', 'Like the rollers on the bottom to turn and fill Works perfectly, and fast! Like the rollers on the bottom to turn and fill. Not a fan of the carafe, (on the larger side), but the overall square design looks great on the countertop. I do prefer cone filters but I would buy this coffee maker again.'),
(7506, 5, 1, 4, '2015-09-04', 'Four Stars Good machine'),
(7507, 5, 1, 3, '2014-10-24', 'Short Life This coffeemaker was great while it lasted. I liked a lot of the features. Sadly, it died after only one year of daily use. I will not buy another.'),
(7508, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-30', 'Nice appearance, good price Good toaster for the money. This is the direct replacement for the one we\'ve had for over 10 years and used on a daily basis - only replaced it because it was really looking it\'s age after thousands of uses. The feature I will miss is the oven rack \"assists\" that pull the hot rack out a few inches when you open the door. Not a deal breaker, but just beware that the rack does not move at all unless you move it.'),
(7509, 6, 1, 1, '2015-09-02', 'Broke after 3 months of light use. Toaster broke after about 3 months (using ~1-2x a week). The handle that you use to push down the toast will not stay down.'),
(7510, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-24', 'Five Stars Very easy to use.'),
(7511, 4, 1, 4, '2016-01-30', 'Works well and settings are pretty accurate! So far so good The door needs a \"spring\" for soft closure.  Works well and settings are pretty accurate!  So far so good!'),
(7512, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-26', 'I like the touch screen and additional options for size and ... This is our second Keirig because we wore the first one out. We upgraded this time with the 2.0. It is simple to use, as well as quick. I like the touch screen and additional options for size and strength. Thank Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(7513, 6, 1, 4, '2014-08-30', 'is better than we have had in along is better than  we have had in along time'),
(7514, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-13', 'works great - top gets extremely hot works great - top gets extremely hot, as typical for toasters. I like how sturdy it is - stays put even on top of the microwave.'),
(7515, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-09', 'Knife toast No complaints at all with this toaster oven. Does anything from toast to heat treat.'),
(7516, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-18', 'Easy to use It was everything I had hoped for in a coffee maker. Easy to use, brews coffee quickly and it is very hot.'),
(7517, 11, 1, 5, '2014-02-09', 'Replaced An Older B&D Unit Bought this updated model to replace an older unit.  It is newer and improved.  State of the art toaster oven.  Best value for the money, does a great job.  Highly recommend.  Tip use the timer feature,  The older one took me a while to figure out that the timer feature is a valuable feature.  Before I started using the timer, had to return home a few times to make sure I turned it off.'),
(7518, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-03', 'This is an excellent alternative, and it really does the task well Heats and toasts evenly, this is where I make my homemade pizzas too, since I don\'t have a luxury of an oven. This is an excellent alternative, and it really does the task well.'),
(7519, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-27', 'Five Stars lightweight and does the job well'),
(7520, 7, 3, 4, '2015-07-06', 'I thought I was going to love the product till I used it and found out you can only put 10oz. of water in it. It has an option to use travel mug, but 10 oz. of water does not even fill half the cup. I was very disappointed in that feature. It makes good coffee, just not enough.'),
(7521, 2, 1, 4, '2016-08-18', 'Works well, with a few little quirks Been needing a toaster oven for a while now and this one works pretty great! It is a little smaller on the inside than anticipated, but it doesn\'t take up a lot of space on my counter, so it\'s a win for me! Knobs are pretty easy to adjust, however, the toaster/timer one is hard to land just right when trying to make barely cooked toast. Also some of the knobs feel a little loose. Like I was expecting a click between the toaster/bake/broil setting and instead it just swivels around. I also feel that there isn\'t a lot of room between the broiler piece and the tray. I\'ve been able to make tuna melts in this toaster oven, but I do have to be careful with how high I stack the toppings. Still, it works and I like it!.'),
(7522, 8, 1, 5, '2016-09-08', 'Five Stars good!.'),
(7523, 10, 1, 2, '2015-09-29', 'Junk It broke after five months. It\'s junk.'),
(7524, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-28', 'We love the new idea. Changing the concept of having a cuppa in the morning was so easy, and no more broken carafs.  Love it'),
(7525, 6, 1, 3, '2015-05-21', 'Well, it\'s fast. It  toast bread really fast, but evenly.'),
(7526, 5, 1, 3, '2015-04-09', 'Makes Cool Coffee I bought this coffee maker as a replacement for a grind and brew that was too much of a pain to clean.  When I brewed my first pot I could immediately tell that the coffee was cooler than my last coffee maker.  Just to be sure I brewed the same amount of water side by side in the two coffee makers.  Sure enough the water from this machine was 10 degrees cooler than my past. Other than how hot the coffee is I really like this machine.  The removable water tank on the bank is helpful as are the \"wheels\" on the bottom.  If you don\'t care about hot coffee this may be the machine for you.  If temperature is very important than keep looking.'),
(7527, 4, 1, 1, '2016-09-21', 'Going to smash this with a sledge-hammer The toaster oven works great, but the beeper alert is loud and obnoxious. It sounds like a fire alarm and scares the dogs. No way to disable it. You have to manually stop the cooking before the beeper goes off.'),
(7528, 6, 1, 5, '2016-11-02', 'Great! Does a good job Great!  Does a good job.'),
(7529, 12, 1, 5, '2014-10-31', 'Still our favorite toaster oven This replaced an older unit, and works just as well or better than the one it replaced.  I like having the \"cancel\" button on the front.'),
(7530, 7, 3, 1, '2015-11-04', 'It did not work well at all, besides the water not getting hot, the screen filter provided left much sediment through in the coffee cup. I promptly returned the item for a refund.'),
(7531, 9, 1, 4, '2015-12-28', 'Four Stars very nice coffee maker!  fairly new so I will see how it holds up then post another review'),
(7532, 1, 1, 4, '2015-07-01', 'Great buy. I love my Keurig Brewing System!  I am the only one who drinks coffee at my house so the convenience of being able to make a single cup is wonderful. I also love the option of using the carafe if family comes over.  I enjoy the variety of coffee available and also being able to use my own coffee or even tea!  A must have.'),
(7533, 8, 1, 5, '2015-08-19', 'works great. a good purchase for the works great.  a good purchase for the price'),
(7534, 6, 1, 5, '2014-09-08', 'Five Stars Great toaster'),
(7535, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-06', 'Great for thin crust pizza!!!! It is a toaster oven, all sides are going to get hot.  The oven size is great for family pizza night.  We were making it as we were eating. It takes about 12-14 mins in the oven at 400.  The key is to keep the crust thin, and keep an eye on it as it cooks.  I wouldn\'t just set it and forget it.'),
(7536, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-14', 'Center section shorted out after 5 weeks Toaster will no longer toast on both sides. Shorted out after 5 weeks. Can not return because it\'s 1 week past 30 day return policy. Will never buy a Cuisinart ever again.'),
(7537, 6, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Five Stars Great toaster. Looks great and great price.'),
(7538, 2, 1, 5, '2016-04-24', 'Love this toaster Love this toaster. Would have liked it even better if the try would slide when you open the door.'),
(7539, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-02', 'Five Stars Really good'),
(7540, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-22', 'I highly recommend purchasing this version of the keurig as it makes ... I just recently recieved my 2.0 keurig as a gift and I couldn\'t have been more ecstatic when receiving it. I find the 2.0 to be extremely user friendly and gives more options than ever before. I highly recommend purchasing this version of the keurig as it makes a fantastic cup of coffee to your liking!'),
(7541, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-15', 'Five Stars We\'re very happy with this coffeemaker. Doesn\'t take up much space and makes great coffee. That\'s what we wanted.'),
(7542, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-15', 'I absolutely love it! I really enjoy it! The touch screen is easy to read and the machine itself is easy to use.'),
(7543, 5, 1, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Works well for us! Makes great coffee. Researched this appliance from other Amazon reviews. I have to agree with the majority of purchasers. Haven\'t had any problems with this coffee maker and really needed a water filter to help with our hardwater from the tap.'),
(7544, 2, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'I am so in love with this oven I am so in love with this oven, it is the best toaster I had in years. Cooks really fast and easy to clean.'),
(7545, 2, 1, 4, '2016-04-26', 'Four Stars The knobs are a little hard to turn but for the price it does all that I wanted'),
(7546, 5, 1, 3, '2015-03-26', 'Two \"standard\" items are an extra charge This HB 46201 Coffee Maker got to my house in the 2 day Amazon Prime/UPS delivery window today. Was disappointed that 2 items normally included with other coffee makers were not included. That\'s the gold permanent filter & the water filter holder with 1 or 2 starter filters. The Manual said these are \"OPTIONAL\". Looked in Amazon for them. They can be purchased for almost $30 additional. WHAT A RIPOFF!! The coffee basket only takes paper filters. Not a very eco friendly design! I make 2 cups of Bold coffee in the morning. My 2 year old GE/Walmart coffee maker takes less than 3 minutes to brew. This HB 46201 took close to 8 minutes. However...It DID make a very good & hot Bold Brew with 1/2 Starbucks Verona & 1/2 Peets Major Dickason\'s.'),
(7547, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-23', 'Love it Cheap simple smoothie maker.  Works well.  Lid leaks if you use it as a glass to drink from.'),
(7548, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Love the Keurig My wife and I love our new Keurig. The conveince of the one cup system is just what we needed. And thank Keurig for the free pods for the review'),
(7549, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-22', 'Five Stars Love this. Perfect single serving blender for smoothies or shakes in the morning.'),
(7550, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-10', 'I didn\'t think I would like the detachable water tank I am very impressed with this coffee maker.  I didn\'t think I would like the detachable water tank.  However, it makes adding water a lot less messy.  I also really like the button settings and the display.  They are very easy to read.  I don\'t know why all coffee makers aren\'t made to be easily readable.'),
(7551, 4, 1, 5, '2016-01-04', 'Five Stars Perfect !!!!'),
(7552, 4, 1, 3, '2015-02-22', 'It works well. It cleans well if you warm ... It works well. It cleans well if you warm or bake items, but does not clean if you broil.  I broiled a small steak and the splatter at the top of the unit would not clean.  I called Cuisinart and they suggested I use vinegar in a warm oven or something called Bartenders Friend, which I could not find.  So I am stuck with a brand new toaster oven that has grease stains imbedded in the top of the oven.'),
(7553, 5, 1, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Best coffee maker I\'ve had Great coffeemaker and easy to clean and use.'),
(7554, 9, 1, 2, '2015-12-01', 'Did we get a lemon? This coffee maker was a disappointment from the moment we set it up.  First, the basket to hold the ground coffee is very small, and does not hold a sufficient amount of coffee to make a full pot.  When we did fill, or overfill in this case, the basket with coffee, the brewing process left a mess of ground coffee inside the cover.  Next, we had several mornings when the coffee dispensed VERY slowly.  Lastly, the coffee began to dispense prior to pushing the dispensing button, and continued to dispense AFTER we released the button.  Within a week we sent this lemon back.'),
(7555, 5, 1, 5, '2016-01-08', 'I looked a long time before selecting this coffee pot ... I looked a long time before selecting this coffee pot and the wait was worth it. Makes delicious coffee, quiet and doesn\'t take up excess room.'),
(7556, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-05', 'Awesome! Mom\'s bday present and she loved it, arrived on time.'),
(7557, 8, 1, 3, '2016-09-17', 'Three Stars Not bad, does the job. Its OK.'),
(7558, 7, 3, 4, '2014-10-25', 'Great alternative for the Keriug K-Cup coffee maker. Cheaper by far and you can also use your favorite ground coffee.'),
(7559, 8, 1, 5, '2016-07-20', 'great cup of coffee I have always had a 10-12 cup coffee pot and always had so much left over so I  thought I would try a smaller one.  I just love it.  Brews a good cup . And brews very quickly.  It doesn\'t stop brewing if you take the pot off before coffee is done but that doesn\'t really matter because it brews so fast'),
(7560, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-17', 'Great Toaster Cuisinart products are quality.  The Cuisinart 2 slice toaster is everything I wanted in a toaster.  Wide slots are great and the ability to bring it up even further when the toast pops up works great.  Also like the ability to choose light and dark for toast.  Also available are settings for defrost, bagels, etc.  I have used for about a month now and highly impressed.'),
(7561, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-20', 'Great Value and Durability This is a great no-frills toaster oven. We use the toaster oven at least once or twice a day as it offers a lot more convenience and far less energy and time over a conventional kitchen oven. Durable, great variety of settings for baking, heating or toasting. Simple to use without a lot of items that could potentially fail. I would recommend this to anyone.'),
(7562, 11, 1, 3, '2014-06-27', 'DOES NOT GET VERY HOT!!! It takes 30 minutes to bake a small frozen pizza at 450 degrees,and it\'s still not all that hot when you get it out.Yeah it\'s small and doesn\'t take a lot of counter space but it also doesn\'t in my opinion work very well.Oh,well I guess for the price is does Ok....'),
(7563, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-10', 'Five Stars works great. Very convenient. Good for the price.'),
(7564, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-08', 'Works Well! Good Value! I bought this toaster oven for our kitchen at work.  It is the perfect size for a small pizza or everyday use for toasting.  It has baking functions that are also easy to use for heating up or cooking appetizers.  It has stood up well to the abuse that comes with shared workplace appliances & continues to work well.'),
(7565, 10, 1, 5, '2016-01-13', 'I used it until I bought a better one - more money good product'),
(7566, 5, 1, 1, '2014-12-09', 'Not a worthwhile investment in great tasting coffee. Really wanted to like this coffee maker but in comparison to our old Capresso MT 500 the coffee it makes is not even close.  It works fine, looks good, has convenient features, etc. but just doesn\'t make a great tasting cup of coffee (with the same inputs as the Capresso).  We went back to the old maker and bought a used one for parts to keep it going.  Either this one is going to landfill or will get donated (which I\'m actually hesitant to do because I\'d rather not have anyone receive a blah tasting cup of coffee).  Not a good purchase for us and a waste of $50 inclusive of a gold tone companion filter (which I have to say also didn\'t work too well).'),
(7567, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-18', 'Five Stars Still working'),
(7568, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-21', 'Five Stars It\'s great'),
(7569, 4, 1, 1, '2015-04-24', 'Died in 2 1/2 years, out of limited warantee Loved the TU, that is until it refused to heat any more. I\'m just glad the poor design and/or quality of parts did not cause a fire in my 2.5 yr old unit. Too late I read this is a common problem with no solution. I wish there was a company that made a model that was as convenient.  It\'s back to the old fashioned toaster. Ugh.'),
(7570, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Good buy. Very nice coffee maker.  2.0 looks more sleek than previous models.  Most Kcup works, if not it is easy to make it work.  Only things I wish are:  water temperature can be adjusted or higher by default  AND hot water size can come in 8 oz (not only 4 or 6 oz). Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7571, 2, 1, 2, '2015-11-12', 'The toaster started emitting this awful burning smell and smoke ... The toaster started emitting this awful burning smell and smoke the first time I turned the temperature above 300F and to the toasting function.  Almost set off the smoke alarm!'),
(7572, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-16', 'Five Stars easy to clean and fits 4 pieces of toaster bread'),
(7573, 6, 1, 5, '2015-02-27', 'Great product. Does a really nice job Great product.  Does a really nice  job. Cleans up easy.'),
(7574, 3, 1, 4, '2015-04-15', 'Just received. Just received and have only cooked one thing but so far really like.  I don\'t understand all the heat complaints as I had this set to 400 and held my hands very close to sides and did not think it was too hot at all.  Did a great job cooking.  Will update as I cook more.  Love the looks of this on my counter as well.  Not too big and not too small.'),
(7575, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-01', 'Five Stars Great Toaster Oven!'),
(7576, 10, 1, 4, '2015-01-01', 'who loved the component that allows you to use the top ... Given as a gift to my son, who loved the component that allows you to use the top as a to-go cup.'),
(7577, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-29', 'Five Stars Love it'),
(7578, 5, 1, 1, '2015-09-14', 'I get coffee grinds in every pot no matter how ... I get coffee grinds in every pot no matter how large or small amount of water I put in.'),
(7579, 12, 1, 2, '2014-11-05', 'Would not recommend I bought this thinking it would be a nice to have to do toast, bagels, etc. Unfortunately it does not work well. You practically have to \"slam\" the lever down for the toaster part for the bread to go into the unit. This is cheaply made. Was going to return and found out I am 4 days late in being able to do so.  Lesson learned.'),
(7580, 11, 1, 2, '2014-04-02', 'Adequate Toaster Purchased this toaster based on user ratings.  It looks good, and is easy to use.  My biggest complaint is how long it takes to make toast.  Takes right at 5 mins. to toast 2 pieces of bread.  WAAAAYYYY too long !  If I hadn\'t thrown away the box it came in, I would be returning this toaster.'),
(7581, 4, 1, 2, '2015-10-30', 'Erratic Cooking Times Considering the cost, I was disappointed in the performance for two reasons: 1. I use this for toasting, and I have the turn the level almost down to the minimum level of \"Light\" in order to get Medium 2. Even more annoying is the inconsistency.  One time the bread is barely warmed; I hit the button again and it\'s practically burnt. Because of this, I have to watch the bread closely every time I use the unit in order to prevent burning.'),
(7582, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-16', 'Great toaster My Mother ask for a toaster for one of her Christmas presents, She had no idea that she was getting this one and she absolutely loves it. I would buy Again and recommend this toaster.'),
(7583, 7, 3, 5, '2016-05-21', 'Great product half the price of Keurug and adjustable cup shelf n only stores water for one making so small space'),
(7584, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-06', 'Excellent Quality I don\'t use this often but when I have it actually fits 6 pieces of toast & works great! The price is an unbelievable value, I had a very expensive toaster oven that I gave up in my dissolution & this is equally good at a fraction of the price!'),
(7585, 3, 1, 4, '2014-10-06', 'Love this oven! Just cooked my first whole chicken! I had to cook it for longer than package said but it came out great. :-) 1 year later: We\'re still using this oven as our main cooking source. It gets used almost daily and the only thing I have yet to figure out is how to clean around the heating elements. But, it cooks great still! I just use a cover for anything greasy so it doesn\'t get on the elements. ______ My gas range died on me and I decided to get this until we can replace it. It\'s been so nice to be able to bake and broil again! It\'s very easy to use, really does fit a 12\" pizza, easy to clean, heats up quickly - even to broil! My favorite function is the beeping and auto-shutoff when you\'re timed food is done. I always forgot to turn the old oven off after baking, now I don\'t have to worry. I purchased a 12\" pizza pan ($6 cheap one) & a 4 piece cooking set (chicago metallic) separately and they both fit this oven. The rubber part of one back foot was missing but came otherwise in perfect new condition. I have it set on the cast iron grates of my broken range so the missing foot piece wasn\'t an issue for me.'),
(7586, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-15', 'Easy to Use. Always ready. I needed a coffee pot that held less than 12 cups, as I like to make fresh throughout the day. It\'s easy to use, always works, and ready when I am.'),
(7587, 5, 1, 4, '2016-11-10', 'Great coffee maker Great coffee maker. Love the programmable feature and the detachable water reservoir. Only issue I have is the plate piece around the buttons/clock falls off all the time.'),
(7588, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-03', 'So disappointed in Cuisinart! I purchased this toaster after much research for a simple 2 slice toaster. It seemed to be the best choice on the market and the name Cuisinart had a very good reputation. I received it in January 2016, after a while it was toasting (bread, bagels, waffles, etc...) on one side and burning the other. I adjusted the settings but no change. The seller kindly replaced the original toaster in hopes it was defective. Well the second one seemed a bit better at the beginning but a few months in it\'s doing the same thing. I suggest if you want a cheap toaster buy the ones for $20 not this one!'),
(7589, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'The best coffee pot I have ever owned The best coffee pot I have ever owned. Great features and easy to use. The only thing that is a little bothersome is the plastic ring on the pot makes it difficult to completely empty it. At least I can pour a cup of coffee without it spilling unlike the Krupps I replaced.'),
(7590, 4, 1, 3, '2015-09-02', 'It is okay It get very hot on top. Cooks quickly. I am still getting use to it.'),
(7591, 10, 1, 5, '2016-06-22', 'Five Stars good.'),
(7592, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Thank you Keurig! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review, I love the Keurig 200 series its easy to use and fast for a quick and go coffee!'),
(7593, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-14', 'Five Stars Love that the water filter can be removed! Nice and sleek design and coffee is done quickly!'),
(7594, 8, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', 'Five Stars The perfect coffee maker for just a cup or two.  I am very satisfied with this purchase.'),
(7595, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-30', 'great product and super easy to use This is truly a great product.  I love the ease of use and the new design.  I love Keurig\'s customer service after purchase as well.  I had some questions and they were professional and courteous.  They even gave me free coffee for reviewing their product.  Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(7596, 6, 1, 5, '2016-02-22', 'Five Stars Nice toaster.'),
(7597, 10, 1, 4, '2015-11-27', 'Does the Job I needed to get a decent blender for making smoothies until I can afford a Vitamix, and I chose this one because it appeared to have the highest wattage in its price range, and the reviews were all fairly solid. I was under the impression that I was getting a blender in the $80 - $100 range for $30 based on the reviews and specs, so I was excited to receive it. Sure enough, it is a pretty solid blender - the pitcher is made of glass and is heavy, which I don\'t mind because that to me means quality. The design is stylish, and the performance is satisfactory. You still have to pick up the pitcher and shake it sometimes when making smoothies, but it does crush the ice well if you add enough liquid (I use light vanilla Silk in mine). I usually let it run for about 30 - 45 seconds to make sure all the ice and nuts get blended. All in all happy with the performance.'),
(7598, 4, 1, 3, '2016-08-22', 'Your aluminum foil partner this oven has given me satisfactory service;it really toasts a bagel.however,the simplest stains do not come off the pull out crumb tray,and the bake/broiler tray.cover the latter with aluminum foil,since the stains are permanent.'),
(7599, 12, 1, 5, '2015-04-23', 'Perfect for my needs So compact. Perfect for my needs!'),
(7600, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-31', 'Great toaster! Light enough to move back into a ... Great toaster!  Light enough to move back into a cabinet after using;  neat slide out crumb tray; lots of temp choices\' nice extra \'lift up\' available so you can reach low toasts;  My favorite toaster ever!  Plus, the price is right!!!'),
(7601, 10, 1, 5, '2015-12-08', 'Five Stars This is great!. I like the size of it. Easy to put in suitcase for travel. Light and practical.'),
(7602, 5, 1, 4, '2017-01-14', 'some super glue fixed it cover up front fell off, the plastic nubs were broken, some super glue fixed it, i still give it 4 stars, great coffee machine.'),
(7603, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-31', 'Perfect! The perfect toaster for perfect toast!'),
(7604, 12, 1, 5, '2016-04-04', 'This is a great product to have for those quick fix it meals This is a great product to have for those quick fix it meals...Doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space which is a major plus. Love it!!! Purchase one for myself and mother.'),
(7605, 10, 1, 2, '2015-07-29', 'Died in less than two months. The motor burned up in less than two months under what I\'d consider very typical use. Only used it four days a week to make one smoothie. One would think it could have handled that.'),
(7606, 6, 1, 4, '2015-06-23', 'I would have liked the adjustment knob to have resistance or be notched It\'s a toaster, it\'s attractive and it toasts well. Not much else to say. I would have liked the adjustment knob to have resistance or be notched. When you wipe it down, it moves too freely and if you don\'t remember to put it back to the selected number, you end up with burnt toast and a smoke filled kitchen.'),
(7607, 6, 1, 5, '2014-01-11', 'Great toaster Browns evenly, does what it advertises - have a two-slice in our RV and a four-slice at home - very satisfied.'),
(7608, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-05', '_____ I\'m very happy with this product , is fast and easy'),
(7609, 3, 1, 4, '2015-09-13', 'and pizza and totally satisfied with it Would actually be 4.5, but closer to 4.  The door handle gets hot, and the door, when opened, just falls down to the table. So I wrapped it with a piece of cardboard, and it looks a bit ugly, but the problem is solved. Otherwise, it works as described, heats up in minutes. Bread doesn\'t toast evenly, though. I didn\'t try to really bake, only used it for roasts, casseroles, and pizza and totally satisfied with it.'),
(7610, 10, 1, 5, '2016-04-20', 'Five Stars Arrive dundamaged an dit works great'),
(7611, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-13', 'One Star It never worked'),
(7612, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-01', 'Very  Happy So far so good.  I\'ve jus had it 3 weeks. No complains for now.'),
(7613, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-08', 'A definite winner Have owned this a couple months now and have to say this is one of the best coffeemakers we\'ve owned. The front access basket is a definite plus. The water reservoir is removable, but I placed my coffeemaker on a rollout stand and am able to easily fill without removing. Very easy to see the fill lines too. I am replacing a Keurig after their fiasco with their new drm machines, and am not regretting it one bit. Have tried four different brands of coffee with similar grinds and all have been good. The unit takes up little counter space. Easy to clean also. The carafe is comfortable to hold and pour.'),
(7614, 4, 1, 1, '2016-10-02', 'New version of TOB-40 junk The design illustrated is no longer made.  I have used an old TOB-40, which looks like the illustration, for about ten years; it has been an excellent appliance.  When I set my new TOB-40 on a counter, instead of standing on four legs it wobbled on two.  The thermostat on the new TOB-40 malfunctions.  In use, it doesn\'t turn the heating elements back on until the oven is too cool, with the result that they stay on until they are bright orange before getting the oven back up to the set temperature, charring whatever I was cooking.  The elements in the old oven never got hotter than a dull red, which did not char food. The first time I washed the crumb tray it bent. I straightened it, and the next time I was careful not to bend it.  It bent again.  I have cleaned the crumb tray in my old TOB-40 innumerable times over ten or so years and it never bent.  The new crumb tray is too flimsy to be cleaned without bending it.  I tried to pull the tray out while the oven was hot and burned myself--that is what the  black insert in the old tray prevented.  Cuisinart used to produce good products; the new TOB-40 is junk.  I have also read a report of a Cuisinart blender bursting apart when the plastic gears broke.  It appears that Cuisinart no longer makes the quality products which built its reputation.'),
(7615, 5, 1, 3, '2016-05-16', 'Great while it worked... I loved this coffee maker.....while it worked. Unfortunately, it stopped working out of the nowhere about 8 months after purchasing it (with normal/average use).'),
(7616, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Quick and easy hot beverages everyday! We purchased the Keurig K250 approximately 30 days ago.  We each enjoy our favorite beverages (coffee, tea, or hot chocolate) every morning.  The process is quick, easy, and with no mess or clean-up.  We are very satisfied with the Keurig K250 and enjoy the flexibility we have to easily enjoy  different beverages everyday.  It\'s much easier to use when preparing a single serving and multiple beverages. Thanks Keuring for the free pod for this review.  Swee'),
(7617, 5, 1, 4, '2015-03-09', 'this is a very good coffee maker the only thing I wished that the warning timer was longer than 2 hours. this is a very good coffee maker.'),
(7618, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-16', 'A keeper waited a long time to find a toaster oven I liked.  This is a keeper.  Heats quickly and evenly.  Very satisfied with this unit.'),
(7619, 11, 1, 4, '2014-07-28', 'Nice toaster oven Nice toaster oven. A bit small after the larger one we had but still big enough to do toast for all and even a quick dinner. Heats and toasts evenly and quickly.'),
(7620, 1, 1, 1, '2015-09-23', 'Sent mine back 1. Makes bad coffee. 2. Will make only 10oz maximum cup even though the box seemed to indicate it would make 12oz cups. 3. Worst of all, it quit working within about a week of receiving it. Or, maybe having it quit might be seen as good since the little K-cups cost close to a dollar each.'),
(7621, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Lovin my new keurig I had the mini K Cup which was nice, but I know have the k250 2.0 brewing system and I am in love. It is the best of both worlds and I love that my travel cups work with it!!'),
(7622, 3, 1, 5, '2015-10-14', 'Five Stars This toaster oven is simple to use and works great.  I would recommend to anyone.'),
(7623, 4, 1, 5, '2015-11-06', 'Best Toaster Oven I have owned this oven for over a year and really love it. Works great as a toaster, to cook small pizzas and lots of other small baking jobs. So easy to clean too by just pulling out the lower tray and wipe clean. I have owned many other taoster ovens and this is by far the best ever.'),
(7624, 12, 1, 4, '2016-12-06', 'Four Stars works great and I have an extra oven to boot.'),
(7625, 4, 1, 4, '2015-10-23', 'This toaster oven has been great since I purchased it in 2013 This toaster oven has been great since I purchased it in 2013. Over time, the door ended up getting \"stuck\" making it more difficult to open. Earlier in 2015 (about 18-20 months later), the door snapped while opening it, sending shards of glass everywhere and bending the metal frame of the door. Thankfully, Cuisinart was great about servicing this as part of their warranty. The new toaster oven has been working even better than the original, without the problems with a \"sticking\" door.'),
(7626, 6, 1, 5, '2016-01-13', 'Exactly what I\'d hoped for Love the simplicity of this design. Works great, I\'ve been using it for almost 2 months. Makes the perfect toast on setting 3 (in my opinion). Easy to clean out from the bottom. Nice short tail of a cord. Everything I need and want and nothing I don\'t. Perfect!'),
(7627, 6, 1, 1, '2015-05-13', 'and then had it replaced through Amazon\'s excellent support plan I purchased one, and then had it replaced through Amazon\'s excellent support plan.  Both toasters behaved the same: in any of the four slots, one side of the bread toasts nicely and the other side is pale.  Very obvious... very undesireable'),
(7628, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-05', 'Great price! Make a great gift! Got this for my brother for Christmas and he has told me over and over what an amazing coffee maker I picked out! Really top notch! Very pleased with it for the price!'),
(7629, 9, 1, 4, '2015-07-03', 'Nice Little Upgrade Really like this coffee machine. It has enough settings to keep most everyone happy that wants just a little more than some cheapie machine. We haven\'t had the issues others are talking about. I love the fuel level indicator and easy push down coffee release lever. Price wise it could be a bit less.'),
(7630, 1, 1, 1, '2016-08-12', 'Disappointed -- Broke after three months I purchased this item less than three months ago and it has stopped working.  From the beginning I had some issues with the Keurig K250.  I found having the water reservoir in the back difficult to use.  I purchased this model because I have a small kitchen and the only place for the coffee maker was on a countertop under a cabinet.  This made it more difficult to access the reservoir.  Also the machine would not brew a cup of coffee unless the water reservoir was filled completely to the water line.  So if I made one cup of coffee and then wanted another, I needed to refill the reservoir to the top even though there was plenty of water left in the tank.  Today while brewing a cup of coffee, the maker refused to shut off and I had boiling water and coffee spill out all over my counter top.  In order to get it to stop, I had to unplug the maker.  I\'ve had other Keurig models for years with no issues, but this model has turned out to be a disappointment.'),
(7631, 5, 1, 3, '2015-03-05', 'Good machine, useful features, doesnt last, long term problem Really enjoyed this machine. Read other reviews for the good features and design. 1.5year- Hot plate is rusting out Control panel trim around the buttons is cracked from heat and moisture and falling off. I guess it depends on what you think the normal life of a machine in this price point should be? Nothing lasts forever..and 3 years probably average life for a Coffee maker in this price level but.. 1.5 years...major issues...not real impressive despite the great design and functioning of this unit.'),
(7632, 6, 1, 3, '2015-05-17', 'Three Stars handle hard to push down. otherwise good'),
(7633, 4, 1, 1, '2015-02-21', 'This is the most inconvenient toaster oven I\'ve ever used ... This is the most inconvenient toaster oven I\'ve ever used.  Even the red light indicator that the unit is on--is on sometimes, and sometimes it is not. I\'m going to ditch this and buy another unit at Walmart that is convenient to use.'),
(7634, 11, 1, 4, '2015-02-23', 'I am very pleased with it Its a big toaster oven. Plus alot of electricity. Very spacious. The color is silver and black. Matches my kitchen decor. I am very pleased with it.'),
(7635, 10, 1, 5, '2016-02-07', 'Attractive and very handy This is a terrific little blender, but you do have to exercise care in using it. I always add liquid first, and even though others have said they can blend with ice, I personally find that hard to believe. I have trouble getting it to blend frozen strawberries without smelling the motor start to overheat. I use it mainly for blending protein powder into juice and adding in other powdered ingredients such as wheat grass and powdered supplements of various kinds. I also use it for blending homemade, organic cosmetics. It works really well for that. A feature that I particularly like is that you can drink right out of the clear, plastic blender compartment, and you can use it to store blended drinks in the refrigerator if you don\'t finish drinking the whole thing at one setting. The blender is easy to take apart and clean as well. This blender would make a great gift for Christmas, birthdays, housewarmings and baby showers. It would work great for blending baby food.'),
(7636, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-07', 'A wonderful gift for my husband to replaced the worn out ... A wonderful gift for my husband to replaced the worn out one we had before. I love that is hard to make a mess on the counter.'),
(7637, 1, 1, 4, '2015-10-07', 'Great Brewer with small 2.0 catch... Works exactly as I expected. Easy to put together and start using. Bought this as a replacement when my small Keurig from 4 years ago finally gave out. The only thing about this new machine is that the KCups must be Keurig branded. I had some older KCups that I used in my previous machine that are not Keurig branded and could not use them with this brewer. Keep that in mind if you\'re replacing an older machine with one of the new 2.0 brewers. Not a huge loss for me but it could be for someone who may have bought KCups in bulk.'),
(7638, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-17', 'Works like a charm. Love the toaster part of it. You Don\'t need much time to toast it.  We have used it for broiling and warming up left overs that the microwave normally makes mushy and the toaster over doesn\'t. I am very pleased with it so far.'),
(7639, 6, 1, 4, '2015-02-17', 'Great toaster!!!  Highly recommended! Toaster works great!  There are several settings for the amount of browning one  prefers. Great with bread, English muffins, and bagels.  .It\'s very easy to clean. Best toaster I have ever owned.  Highly recommended.'),
(7640, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'A Few bumps getting satarted I was \"gifted\" a K-250.  I had a VERY hard time reading your instruction book (print TOO SMALL, print not Dark enough, and answers came in red that does not show well on the paper used) .. Now to the machine.  I am TOTALLY satisfied.  It is clean, quick, EASY TO USE, and makes great tasting fresh coffee. .I\'m sipping a cup of Kahlua as we speak.  DELICIOUS!  So far I have had no problems with needles clogging, filter, heating, and delivery into my cup, no spills, no drips. If I get coffee for this review I like Nantucket, and Kahlua.  Thank you for this great coffee system.'),
(7641, 2, 1, 1, '2016-06-03', 'One Star it only fits a 6 inch pizza'),
(7642, 4, 1, 4, '2015-04-24', 'There is a NEWER TOB-40 Custom Classic Toaster Oven!! I bought this toaster oven on AMZN almost 4 years ago.  It has a 3 year warranty. I have gotten a lot of use out of this little oven and it has performed well.  I have kept it clean and the crumb tray empty.  Recently I noticed the right side, lower front element is \"bulging\" a bit.  It doesn\'t burn any brighter than the other elements, but it might explode or split open soon.  Amazing how many reviews mention this and yet Cuisinart has NOT recalled the item.  Time to replace this toaster!! UPDATE May 2, 2015:  I noticed that this same model has been updated.  I found it at Bed, Bath, and Beyond for $79.99 and used my 20% off coupon to bring down that price.  Looks identical except for the improvements.  The difference is that the crumb tray is all silver (no black) and slides in and out easier.  And most importantly, the heating elements have been structured without those white \"knobs\" on the inside.  Maybe that change will keep them from warping.  AMZN is selling the old product.'),
(7643, 3, 1, 1, '2016-09-21', 'Two ovens down and again a fire I am on my second oven and again this morning it has caught on fire.  I usually just use it for toast and sometimes baking chicken or heating up a pizza.  I always use foil on the bottom pan for any drippings---and clean the pan also, so I don\'t understand what is happening. I saw another review, so today I sent out an email to the email address given with a photo of the oven (with baking powder all over). I really do like this oven, but the repeat fires is something they need to check into.  I will re-write if I receive an answer from the company.'),
(7644, 5, 1, 2, '2016-10-31', 'Two Stars face plate broke after about 3 weeks.  Trashed it.'),
(7645, 5, 1, 5, '2014-12-18', 'Love This Coffee Maker Best, Most User Friendly Coffee Maker ever made.'),
(7646, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-07', 'Five Stars I love this toaster.  I have toasted wheat bread, bagels, English muffins, ciabatta and Italian.  All toasted perfectly.'),
(7647, 2, 1, 4, '2015-07-12', 'It works but tray could be larger. Yeah the first time it had a definite plastic smell when preheating. But the main problem is the tray that comes with it could be a little bit wider (an extra half inch would still fit perfectly) for baking small things when I don\'t want to heat up a whole oven. I haven\'t tried it as an actual toaster for bread because I have an actual toaster because these things never toast evenly and get zebra stripes when toasted compared to a real toaster. And to add I have no idea how you are supposed to fit 4 slices of bread in it. I can only see putting 2 into it if it was actually used as a regular toaster. Update still working perfectly. Great for little things like heating up slices of pizza etc... Just still need  anew baking tray that is slightly larger. No problem with food bursting into flames or handle melting off yet but time will tell. This is the last update unless something bad happens which I doubt. Since I am actually competent and know how to work things and know knot to leave them alone when in use. Update 9/30/15: Gave in an extra star because I recently started making small loaves of bread and realized I didn\'t own a cooling rack (In the regular oven). And I looked at the toaster oven and got an idea, the wire rack inside of it doubles as a nice small cooling rack, great for small loaves of bread. I still need to get one for cakes and larger items but that was a nice little bonus That I didn\'t have to find a store open at midnight to get one. Just be sure to clean it well if you cook greasy food on it and plan to cool baked or pastry type items. By the way you NEVER leave any appliance alone that has a heating element. My spouse has managed to set every toaster oven that we have ever owned on fire by using it improperly and leaving it alone, yet I never have a problem.'),
(7648, 6, 1, 5, '2015-07-02', 'Toast for a toaster. Very nice toaster!'),
(7649, 8, 1, 3, '2016-07-14', 'Three Stars Think hotel room coffee maker.  Seems well built.  No issues thus far.'),
(7650, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-19', 'Worked great for me! I don\'t typically write reviews. But on this blender I am. 5 star_.'),
(7651, 3, 1, 5, '2016-07-25', 'but so far so good. I\'ve only used it for toasting bread and ... I\'ve only had this for about a month, but so far so good.  I\'ve only used it for toasting bread and reheating food.  The controls are easy to use and it toast sliced bread to perfection.'),
(7652, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-12', 'So nice I really am enjoying my new Keurig. It works great.'),
(7653, 9, 1, 5, '2015-12-17', 'No leaks! Very happy with this. Have had several of the Hamilton Beach version but they leak constantly. This one is far better!'),
(7654, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-19', 'After all this time it works perfectly After all this time and daily use is still works perfectly'),
(7655, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-25', 'Won\'t brew a large pot of coffee Worst coffee maker EVER!  Bought to replace my leaky Cuisinart Grind & Brew, which we used faithfully for over 7 years.  This thing won\'t even brew a full pot!  I don\'t know where all the water goes, but it wasn\'t in my pot after an hour of being on and untouched.  In addition, what was in the pot were GROUNDS!  Tried brewing on Bold and Regular with same results.  Not a happy camper!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(7656, 6, 1, 1, '2015-01-04', 'Makes toast if you don\'t care if it is uneven ... Makes toast if you don\'t care if it is uneven, i.e. one side toasted, the other is raw. Purchased on Nov, 2014. a real piece of junk. I waited too long to return it, so I sold it in a garage sale. I\'m now looking for another toaster. Shame on Cuisinart for producing such a shoddy product.'),
(7657, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-13', 'Five Stars WORKS WELL SO FAR'),
(7658, 1, 1, 1, '2015-06-24', 'How can they make new products worse -- to increase sales, maybe? I purchased this smaller model after a previous Keurig  one cup machine quit  working (it was 4 years old and used daily) -- I do feel I got my money\'s worth out of the older model.  The  newer, smaller model has the most annoying noise while its heating up water and then dispensing it.  it goes \"ka-chunk, ka-chunk, ka-chunk\" until the cup is full.  After using  it twice a day for less than a month, it started acting up -- when programmed for an 8 oz, cup, it would not shut off -- it continued to dispense water and overfilled a 12 oz  capacity mug and there was coffee all over the counter.  I unplugged the unit and cleaned up the mess.  Thinking  I had programmed it wrong, I plugged it back in, I again hit the 8 oz selection and it pumped water through until the \"add water\" thing came on.  it is going back -- first negative review I think I have ever given.  darn and no coffee in the morning either'),
(7659, 7, 3, 1, '2015-08-02', 'When my last machine died after 3 years I thought I\'d try another manufacturer. This machine worked well for 21 cups or so, then it just quit. Something plugged in the pump system, no way to repair. In the garbage it goes and back for another Kuerig.'),
(7660, 2, 1, 4, '2016-10-26', 'It works just fine and we like the smaller size which just fits ... This is our first toaster oven. It works just fine and we like the smaller size which just fits our available counter space. It does toast well, but is a bit slow. Also, if food or toast is ready before timer goes off, there is no way to shut off the timer, so it simply has to run itself out. We would feel better if we could save the electricity.'),
(7661, 11, 1, 4, '2014-03-21', 'Terrific but maybe too small This little unit has worked very well so far .  I say little because it is smaller than my last B & D toaster oven (old!) and presents some issues. But it has all the same bells and whistles, so I am happy.  The biggest complaint about its small size is the distance between the heat element and the racks on top.  I now have to buy thinly configured sweet potatoes when I bake them.  And I know that any kind of casserole dish will not fit.  But for people who do not serve large portions or for singles, this is ideal. The one tray seems to be very cleanable--probably teflon.  It usually wipes clean without scouring; overtime that will no doubt change.  And I usually insert some alum foil under a fish or meat portion when I roast/broil.  The controls are very complete for such a small and very inexpensive item. It is solid, heavy and compact so that it doesn\'t take room on the counter.  It has the bell that ends the time cycle which is easy to control and well marked.  It heats up remarkably fast and I usually do not preheat as recommended.  I would suggest that the design engineers add about 1 inch depth to the rack spacing, and I do not like the fact that the cooking tray slides in below the rack in such a way that the rack overlaps with some open space on the sides--allows for some drippage, I think, although so far I have been careful about that.  I think added depth to allow for a return to the old-fashioned side slots to hold the drip tray would improve this and make it even more functional.  But for the vey low price, I think this is a bargain.  (BIG Caveat:  I have had it only a month or so!)'),
(7662, 8, 1, 4, '2016-10-15', 'Reasonable pricing for an individual serving coffee maker. So far so good.'),
(7663, 4, 1, 3, '2015-02-07', 'No Timer! It\'s probably my fault but I did not notice that this unit didn\'t have a built in timer... Previous to this, I had a GE oven and I was hoping for the same features. Yes, I have a timer on the microwave but it\'s just not as functional as having one included on the oven .  It cooks evenly, cleans up nicely but my expectations were not met... my fault for not reading the fine print.'),
(7664, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-14', 'wonderul Product. This toaster is even more beautiful than pictured-if that\'s possible for a toaster. It is wonderful. Definitely recommend to anyone!'),
(7665, 6, 1, 3, '2014-03-19', 'Unfortunately, first one received cannot be properly rated Toaster was good for the four times (!!) it was used before it decided not to work at all. Assumed it was just a fluke, so returned to Amazon for same item. Could not have been easier and quicker. Had new one in a couple of days and it\'s happily doing it\'s thing very well. Hopefully for a good long time.'),
(7666, 5, 1, 1, '2016-08-24', 'Dont\' Buy! Buyer Beware! ! ! Bought this Hamilton Beach 12-cup coffee maker on 7-8-2016 and it stopped working on 8-23-2016. Lasted only 6 1/2 weeks. And of course it is pass the 30 day return policy and can not return to Amazon for a replacement or a refund. Looks like I am out $38.99. I won\'t be buying any electronic items from Amazon every again. Better off going to a store to buy one, since the store will let you return a 6 1/2 week purchase.'),
(7667, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-31', 'It works great! I use this product every day.  It works great!'),
(7668, 9, 1, 5, '2016-05-16', 'A wonderful idea. What a great invention!  The coffee stays hot and fresh for two hours, and still tastes good longer than that when it\'s reheated.  No bitter tarry burnt taste.  I\'m surprised all the other small appliance companies aren\'t selling an equivalent product.  Or, maybe they are, because I haven\'t looked for a replacement.  We\'ve had ours for more than five years and it still works great.'),
(7669, 5, 1, 1, '2016-06-30', 'It definitely looks nice, but after a use or two you start ... I\'ve had this coffee maker for only about 2 weeks.It definitely looks nice, but after a use or two you start seeing how cheaply made it really is. Filling to the 12 cup line only brews about 10 cups. Almost immediately it became apparent the the casing covering the control and display area is not very well secured. It pops lose every time you open the area below to put in the coffee grounds. You have to pop it back in every time you use it. I just don\'t see this coffee maker having a very long life in one piece. It\'s about the quality I would expect from a $15-$20 machine but at about twice the price.'),
(7670, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-09', 'Five Stars good'),
(7671, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-10', 'Quite the toaster oven There isn\'t much to say about this toaster oven. But it can bake broil toast and warm perfectly.'),
(7672, 11, 1, 3, '2015-12-30', 'Easy to clean, but hard to use for bread slices. Takes a while to figure out how to simply toast bread. I still can\'t get an even toast, with or without the crumb tray in place. Occasionally the timer will finish but won\'t trigger the unit to stop heating. Decent for heating up pizza slices or muffins... Not the best unit I\'ve used. However, it\'s easy to clean!'),
(7673, 9, 1, 5, '2016-07-19', 'Cusinart DCC-3000 Cofee-on-Demand 12-Cup Makes great coffee, easy to use.'),
(7674, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-01', 'Just what I needed I have had toaster ovens for over 30 years; when I needed a new one about 6 years ago, I bought one with a timer (as most of them do), and found it impossible to consistently set the toaster, so I returned it and bought this Cuisinart. Happy, happy, happy that toasting is reliable and consistent, and while larger than the old school toaster ovens, this one is not too humongous. I am a bagel junkie - I buy them from a Jewish bakery across town, 2 dozen at a time, slice and freeze them, and put one, frozen, in the toaster oven each morning, to produce a wonderful bagel that is crunchy/chewy on the outside and soft/warm on the inside. After 5 years of daily use, for toasting, reheating, and broiling (I live alone, so I use this toaster oven for everything!), one of the heating elements started to split, so I ordered another (God forbid I should spend one day without my toaster oven!). However, the new one is still in the box in a closet, as over a year later the old one is still working well, even with the filament split along nearly its entire length. I don\'t know why so many people insist on having a toaster oven with a timer... I don\'t have a timer on my oven; so I don\'t need one on my toaster oven. Dependable, repeatable toaster settings are what\'s important to me.'),
(7675, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-06', 'COMPACT, CUTE AND FUNCTIONAL Nice little pot, and it fits in a very small space, which is all I had. Coffee is good. I don\'t need a timer or a clock on my coffeemaker so this is just right. Good price and it arrived quickly. I have a Black & Decker one cup coffee maker and like that one also - I\'ve had it for 3 years and it still works great. My electric drill and screw driver is Black & Decker and when one dies, I buy another because they charge quickly and work great. I would not have thought of Black & Decker as synonymous  with \"coffeemaker\" - but I\'m happy with them just the same. Another Amazon winner!'),
(7676, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-04', 'Five Stars This is a great product, I love how easy it is to use and to clean'),
(7677, 10, 1, 2, '2015-04-09', 'Two Stars Broke after two days.'),
(7678, 6, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Five Stars Does a great job on english muffins'),
(7679, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Keurig 2.0 - Convenient and sleek I love my Keurig 2.0 Brewing System. My family and I enjoy brewing coffee a few times a day. The Keurig 2.0 System is convenient and easy to use. It has a sleek design and is visually pleasing. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7680, 6, 1, 5, '2015-03-13', 'Five Stars Fantastic toaster!! If you need a basic toaster then this is it!'),
(7681, 3, 1, 4, '2014-11-05', 'Four Stars Works really good, the outside of the oven gets super hot, just dont have anything close around it'),
(7682, 8, 1, 5, '2014-10-01', 'GREAT GREATLY CHEAP..'),
(7683, 1, 1, 4, '2016-01-25', 'Expensive Device Very convenient and versatile.  It gives so much flexibility.  However, you get a preselected amount of coffee which may be weaker or stronger than you want.'),
(7684, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Great Office Addition Thank you for the two free pods for writing this review.  I love the color of my Keurig,, turquoise, which is a great color.  The coffee tastes great, and the convenience is wonderful.  It is a real asset to the office, and makes it more pleasant to be at work.  Everyone is so pleased to come to work, and make a good drink to get the workday started right.'),
(7685, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Perfect coffee maker This coffee maker is just perfect. It serves great tasting coffee enough for family and friends.'),
(7686, 4, 1, 5, '2015-04-14', 'Amazing I love my toaster oven :) so happy I purchased this :)'),
(7687, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-10', 'love it so much I can\'t rave about this product enough! Its easy to put together and set up. I love that its compact so it doesnt take up much counter space and the touch screen is  pretty cool feature.its very easy to use I didn\'t even need the manual to use the touch screen. And it has so many different KCUPS drinks to choose from, something for everyone. I received this product for free for product testing from inflinster.'),
(7688, 4, 1, 5, '2015-08-29', 'love it long time I\'ve been using this toaster for years and it is fantastic! I love the size, it often allows us to use it as an oven replacement. The multiple options for the rack height is very useful for fitting tall things. I don\'t miss the timer for bake and broil... I have a timers on my oven and microwave, don\'t need a third. The toast light-dark knob is perfect, incidentally it correlates directly to time if you\'re hung up on the timer thing.'),
(7689, 5, 1, 1, '2015-02-10', 'Died after 9 months, terrible \"warranty\" This coffeemaker was great and had all the features I wanted, but only lasted 9 months. It suddenly stopped drawing any power, and it wasn\'t on at the time, nor was there a power outage. It failed while still under warranty, but Hamilton Beach\'s \"customer service\" obviously doesn\'t stand behind the product, as they make you pay for shipping both ways. This is a way for them to both deter customers from filing a warranty claim in the first place and, failing that, to recoup even more money from the customer that they already bilked once by selling him or her a shoddy product. I will never buy another Hamilton Beach product.'),
(7690, 11, 1, 5, '2015-02-15', 'Works like a dream Works like a dream! My very first toaster oven so I had some reservations about it but it does a great job. The only thing I notice that it has a hard time with is cooking at longer temperatures for baking. I usually have to bake the item longer then if I would have had to in the normal oven.'),
(7691, 12, 1, 3, '2014-03-21', 'Purchased for the second time My husband and I liked our toaster oven so much we decided to replace it with the same one. However, the rack and pan in the oven get stuck and cause it not to open. It has to be forced open.'),
(7692, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Great Gift for my Grandfather I purchased this brewer through Keurig\'s own website as a gift for my grandfather. I was concerned that he may have issues with it, given that he is not a tech person and this brewer uses a touchscreen. However, he has been having a very easy time using it and loves it. It is durable and brews a great cup of coffee. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. ~kemu1772'),
(7693, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-30', 'Just as advertised! This is a very small, but mighty, toaster oven. I bought it for a very small kitchen, not wanting to use up much counter space. It arrived right on time and was plug-in ready. The inside just fits a sliced bagel or small Corningware dish but the cover has to be inverted to fit. It does just what I needed with less energy usage than the electric oven. The only downside for me is that the cord is too short so I have to move it over each time but that is OK. Nice little oven for reheating or toasting for one.'),
(7694, 1, 1, 5, '2015-09-23', 'Very Happy So far I\'ve been using my Keurig daily for about a month and couldn\'t be happier! Looks very nice and isn\'t noisy at all in my opinion. It\'s been a perfect fit for my college dorm. Yes, as another reviewer mentioned there is sometimes condensation built up around the top of the reservoir lid but it hasn\'t been an issue for me. Would definitely recommend this Keurig. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(7695, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-05', 'Fantastic product for the price Fantastic product for the price. We\'ve been using it regularly since it arrived and it\'s made food prep very easy. Make sure to keep at eye on the oven feature when using it. Sometimes we overestimate the temperature/time requirements and end up burning the food.'),
(7696, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-22', 'Great Toaster Oven The burning plastic smell definitely happened the first time I turned it on, but I just let it run at a low temp for 20 minutes when I first got it and when I used it the first time it was fine. Cooks things accurately and temps seem to be accurate in general. Small, but a great size for snacks/ one or two person cooking. Its a great size and fits on the counter without taking up too much space.'),
(7697, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-25', '5 Stars Super Easy to use, blends smoothies perfectly. I love the single serve aspect. For $15 it truly is 5 star quality/value. Just wash and re use.'),
(7698, 4, 1, 1, '2016-01-19', 'this is fine. For anything else If you are making toast, and want a giant toaster, this is fine.  For anything else, make sure you have a fire extinguisher handy.  I previously had the TOB-100, which I ultimately bought again, immediately after buying this one.  It has none of the safety features of the TOB-100.  The only thing on a timer is the toast.  The slightest mistake in setting the controls can set you on broil instead of bake.  And you will have to use a separate timer. To top it all off, this one came without one of the parts, the grill rack.  Cuisinart is sending me another, but I don\'t even think I will donate this.  It is too dangerous.  Stay away.  Spend more, and get the TOB-100, or another higher-end model.  This is a disaster waiting to happen.'),
(7699, 8, 1, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Five Stars Good product.'),
(7700, 12, 1, 5, '2015-12-15', 'It\'s more compact than her old one and fits her kitchen much better. She loves it and uses it all the ... Bought it for my mom as she really wanted a combo oven. It\'s more compact than her old one and fits her kitchen much better. She loves it and uses it all the time!'),
(7701, 6, 1, 5, '2016-12-10', 'Five Stars Smell of something first few toast.'),
(7702, 4, 1, 2, '2015-01-07', 'Don\'t bother unless you\'re buying a disposable toaster oven Worked fine for almost exactly one year, then wouldn\'t turn off. Unplugged it, and it won\'t turn back on. Given the cost to ship it back and the $10 fee for warranty repair, we\'ve decided to buy a different toaster oven and not buy another Cuisinart product. I\'d call their practices \"shameful,\" but it\'s obvious that Cuisinart is now incapable of shame.'),
(7703, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-02', 'perfect for a busy kitchen so many great things about this maker- the water canister is plastic and easy to fill to result in less of a chance of breaking the pot, the filter pops out from the front so you dont need to pull this from under the counter. overall im really impressed at te ease of use. the coffee is okay- not the best ive ever had...but certainly you cant complain.'),
(7704, 5, 1, 2, '2015-11-24', 'I\'m disappointed. We have only had this coffee pot for a short time.  Not even a month. The glass pot broke already.  I am shocked. I have never had that happen to me in all my years of owning a coffee maker.  I don\'t even wash my coffee pots in the dishwasher because I\'m afraid they will break in there.  I\'m disappointed.'),
(7705, 5, 1, 4, '2016-04-30', 'Four Stars Works well'),
(7706, 2, 1, 5, '2016-07-18', 'Works great as both This toaster oven is everything I hoped it would be! Works great as both, cleanup is extremely easy due to the tray in the bottom that can be removed to clean. We bake whole chicken in it as well as cooking many meals. Love, love, love.'),
(7707, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Keurig 2.0 series Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review! Love this machine and have heard wonderful things about it!'),
(7708, 12, 1, 5, '2016-03-03', 'Five Stars Great product'),
(7709, 12, 1, 5, '2015-07-28', 'Great buy I was hesitant on the looks of this toaster. My entire kitchen is red so of course I went for the red one. I chose the older model due to it having way better reviews. I\'m so glad I purchased this, great buy. People have complained about it toasting unevenly. I haven\'t really had that issue. I did toast egg rolls in it and the outer edges burnt up a bit, but what do you expect for the cost? Other than that no issues and I love it! Way faster than waiting for my entire oven to heat up to cook something small!'),
(7710, 2, 1, 4, '2016-01-26', 'Had it 6 months, no problems. This is a toaster oven. Everything is great except I wish the timer had a cancel option-- you can\'t turn it off early, you just have to take your toast or whatever out early and let the timer run down.'),
(7711, 5, 1, 2, '2016-04-28', 'Two Stars The front face plate fell right off only days after using it, Had to send it back !!'),
(7712, 1, 1, 2, '2016-02-17', 'It worked for a while, but... I purchased this back in July 2015 for my new office at work.  It worked fantastic...until now.  Now it is constantly saying that it is preheating when not actually doing anything.  Then when I finally do get to brew a cup of coffee (by unplugging the machine and plugging it back in to reset whatever was stuck), it seems to brew whatever size that it wants to.  I just selected the largest cup, but it only gave me a third of a cup of coffee.  Other times it will overflow.  Not sure what\'s happening but I\'m highly disappointed in Keurig.  This was a lot of money just to die in 7 months.'),
(7713, 4, 1, 4, '2015-02-01', 'It does a good job baking and broiling It does a good job baking and broiling, Be careful with the toaster/bagel shade setting, it toasts dark on a low shade setting. The baking pan and broiling rack are very flimsy as compared to my previous Cuisinart Classic Toaster Oven.'),
(7714, 12, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'So Glad I found This! My husband wanted a toaster oven after the regular toaster died. I did not want a large kitchen appliance sitting on the counter so I found this HB Toastation combination toaster and oven.  We both love it and it looks beautiful sitting on the black counter.  We are just two people and it is perfect for us. Would not recommend for a large family.'),
(7715, 5, 1, 5, '2014-07-18', 'Five Stars Love it and the reservoir for the water.'),
(7716, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-05', 'Five Stars Excelent'),
(7717, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-18', 'It\'s helping me kick my diet soda habit So easy to set up and so convenient! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7718, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-22', 'Love it! A great coffee pot! Love the attached container to fill with water.  It did take a while to figure out how to put the coffee basket inside the holder due to its shape, but once you see the \"flat\" side, it\'s easy. I have bought a Bunn, Keurig, etc. and this one is much cheaper and the coffee tastes good.'),
(7719, 5, 1, 5, '2015-11-30', 'Five Stars Makes excellent coffee when using the easy to program brew setting for stronger flavor.'),
(7720, 7, 3, 5, '2016-03-28', 'We use this as our travel coffee maker to use at hotels. Coffee is hot, and ready in minutes. Love this.'),
(7721, 9, 1, 5, '2015-02-20', 'Five Stars We are enjoying this product.'),
(7722, 10, 1, 4, '2016-02-17', 'Doesn\'t blend the ice as good as I wish it would I use this everyday for my shakes. Doesn\'t blend the ice as good as I wish it would. It also broke once but my dad fixed it and has been working ever since. Very handy, could be better though.'),
(7723, 9, 1, 1, '2015-04-25', 'Coffee-on-Floor This coffee maker rots. At least 5 times, I have had to clean a river of expensive steamy coffee off the floor and from behind the refrigerator because the spring in the reservoir breaks. Also, if you fill the basket all the way with grounds enough to make strong coffee, the whole reservoir fills with grounds. I am not overfilling it and I am using the amount of grounds recommended in the manual per cup. Last, there is no good way to clean the cover of the reservoir and the hinge which gets full of grounds every time. Cuisinart has replaced the reservoir free of charge every time but that doesn\'t solve what is an obvious design flaw. I am hoping they will replace it with a different coffee maker of lesser value.'),
(7724, 4, 1, 4, '2015-03-08', 'Great little oven for the price! We use this guy every day and it\'s a great little oven for the price'),
(7725, 12, 1, 4, '2014-03-12', 'Small toaster/oven It is just right if you want a decent toaster that doubles as a very small oven. I cut a muffin in half and lay it sideways. The toaster will hold two halves of a bagel with little bit of coaxing. It has no bells and whistles, literally, and that\'s fine by me.'),
(7726, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-13', 'Five Stars The ideal toaster oven.'),
(7727, 2, 1, 5, '2016-09-08', 'Five Stars just what I wanted.'),
(7728, 10, 1, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Easy to use, very quiet and does its job. This is simply the best protein shake blander!'),
(7729, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-18', 'Love it I love this thing.  We owned the previous model which was great too, though a pita to fill the water reservoir.  I was thrilled to see they changed that design; the water reservoir is removable with easy to read markings.'),
(7730, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-19', 'good good'),
(7731, 2, 1, 4, '2016-02-17', 'not a good buy. As with them all The knob that turns the thing on is really hard to turn. For frail elderly, not a good buy. As with them all, this one has to be watched or it will burn your item. On the good side it does do the trick if watched....'),
(7732, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-31', 'So far so good So far so good.  The coffee maker is a clean design and looks nice sitting on the counter.  It brews great tasting coffee super fast. We use this every day and have had no problems. Easy to clean. I recommend it to you all!'),
(7733, 9, 1, 5, '2016-01-30', 'Great buy! Coffee maker is awesome ! Easy to operate  and coffee brews up delicious. I like the fact that it doesn\'t have a carafe.'),
(7734, 4, 1, 1, '2016-04-03', 'Low quality, Cuisinart just put their name on some junk. Had one of the heating elements sag after about 1 year and stop working.'),
(7735, 12, 1, 5, '2015-01-24', 'Five Stars Broil Bake and Toast....it does and very well'),
(7736, 11, 1, 4, '2014-07-03', 'temperature dial Pros: This is an oven toaster that is well made.  It\'s compact enough to put on a counter without looking like a sore thumb, but yet has room for 4 slices of standard size bread.  It toasts accurately according to the set dial.  Awesome price! Cons: I wished it would just provide an option to turn the dial directly to the desired toast temp without turning the dial first to the \"10\" mark then back to the desired toast temp.  This way there is less room for errors.'),
(7737, 6, 1, 5, '2014-06-11', 'WELL worth the money I have tossed 2 other toasters in last 2 years so this time I spent a little more.  We have other Cuisinart products that work well and this one is no exception.  Toasts very evenly on BOTH sides..  How about that! Does great on bagels, etc as well.  Great toaster'),
(7738, 7, 3, 5, '2016-09-15', 'Was easy to operate. Fits neatly in my small kitchen. Like all the features a single serving or more, inexpensive and not to bulked. This coffeemaker is what I had been looking for. Wish someone had recommend it when it first appeared on the market.'),
(7739, 5, 1, 1, '2016-03-31', 'I was happy with this until today I was happy with this until today. The carafe broke and I have spent an hour on the internet looking for a replacement. Hamilton Beach doesn\'t have it and neither does anyone else. Really ticks me off.'),
(7740, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-28', 'Love it! It looks stylish and is easy to ... Love it! It looks stylish and is easy to clean. It toasts very quick so you have to be careful. I like how it has many functions, not just toasting.'),
(7741, 10, 1, 5, '2016-09-05', 'Thanks for a great product. I insist on having the blade on the bottom of the container rather than have to flip  the container after running the unit. This is replacing one I used regularly for 5 years.. Thanks for a great product.'),
(7742, 5, 1, 5, '2015-05-27', 'Love this coffee maker Love this coffee maker! This might be the perfect coffee maker, especially under $100! Great features: swing out basket makes it much more flexible under cabinets & much less messy to empty & fill. The swivel wheels allow it to spin, but do not slid all over the counter. The stainless steel fits well with my appliances. Most importantly the coffee tastes great!'),
(7743, 5, 1, 5, '2016-04-30', 'Five Stars Fast delivery enjoying every morning'),
(7744, 3, 1, 3, '2015-06-09', 'Nice oven but not for a 12\" pizza I returned this  It was an acceptable quality but didn\'t fit a 12\" pizza without forcing it closed; and then the back of the pizza cooked and the front was still not cooked.  It would be fine for other things but we primarily used countertop ovens for toast or pizza.  Then I ordered that new Oster (I was replacing an old Oster I\'d liked) and that was a true cheapo product.  So I broke down an ordered a Breville......'),
(7745, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-27', 'Five Stars best coffeepot I ever owned, more features than more expensive models, would highly recommend.'),
(7746, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-03', 'Five Stars Best coffee maker ever owned. Hated the carafe and hot plate that always seemed to rust in traditional makers.'),
(7747, 9, 1, 5, '2015-09-02', 'Five Stars Very good choice! I highly recommend it'),
(7748, 2, 1, 5, '2015-09-02', 'Five Stars Looks sleek and works great'),
(7749, 5, 1, 5, '2015-09-19', 'A great coffee maker Pros: Carafe doesn\'t drip! Reliably makes great coffee. Intuitive design - easy to program. Cons: when rinsing out the carafe, a little water stays in the carafe, impossible to shake out without sticking your hand in to wipe it with a cloth; not a huge problem, just annoying for my OCD side haha. Also more annoying than an actual con: the backlight is suuuuper bright, casting shadows in my little one-room studio. All in all a great coffee maker; would definitely buy again!'),
(7750, 7, 3, 4, '2016-12-16', 'Good product'),
(7751, 12, 1, 5, '2016-08-09', 'Recommend Wonderful,  finally we got product two in one, perfect.'),
(7752, 2, 1, 5, '2016-05-24', 'good looking and working toaster oven I love this toaster oven, it matches the other stainless steel appliances we have and it does a very good job of toasting bread etc.'),
(7753, 7, 3, 5, '2015-05-06', 'Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffee Maker, 49997, Black. I am really happy with this coffee maker, no more making half pot of coffee - when I only want one cup. The adjustable cup holder comes in handy. The feature I really like the best is that it takes the k-cup packs great for when I want a treat :). The unit is very easy to clean after each use. The coffee maker takes up little space on the counter. After having a few weeks I find myself going for this coffee maker :). And enjoying a fresh cup of coffee, rather than making a whole pot of coffee in my other coffee pot and it sitting for hours. Love this coffee maker.'),
(7754, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Got this as a birthday gift and I absolutely love it. So simple to use Got this as a birthday gift and I absolutely love it. So simple to use. Definitely a big help when you have a busy life with being a wife, having a toddler and going to college. Just stick a cup under it and press a button. In less than half a minute you have a delicious cup of coffee. Can\'t wait to try all the different varieties of K-cups. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7755, 1, 1, 4, '2015-08-24', 'Great tasting Coffee ! I just received this new Keurig 2.0 in white. Coffee is hot and great tasting. Very simple. No clock or timer . You must use the new Keurig 2.0 k cups. The older K cups do not work. The carafe is bought separate . It just sits against the machine doesn\'t click . No bells and whistles with this model but it does come in a lot of great colors and the design looks great. This is great for the college student or people looking for very simple. Great tasting hot coffee! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(7756, 9, 1, 4, '2016-02-19', 'Great coffeepot This is clean, neat and great coffee pot.  It took me a few tries to find the right mix of coffee per water, and I wish there were another way of emptying the pot. But all around I love it and would buy it again.'),
(7757, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-11', 'Five Stars Like it very much.oven big enough for me to roast meat for the two of us'),
(7758, 2, 1, 4, '2015-12-06', 'Affordable, will do the small jobs. Great, affordable little oven. However, there is only room for a shallow dish inside - not much room between the slide-out shelf and the heaters.'),
(7759, 6, 1, 3, '2014-09-08', 'Disappointed This toaster is not as good as I had expected. Even though I can toast four slices of bread at once, I have to push the bread into the slot because it does not readily accommodate the width of the bread.  Unless they use very thin bread, I would not recommend this to friends.'),
(7760, 2, 1, 5, '2016-02-24', 'Works great for the purpose its designed Works great for the purpose its designed, considering its price. You can not cook a regular meal in it (size is pretty small), but it is sufficient for cooking a pizza, warming small things, toasting of course, and melting butter. It is quite compact and pretty on a counter top. Before this unit, I had  purchased a more expensive model, but returned it. This one is a keeper. Have been using it for over 7 months now, and am still happy'),
(7761, 4, 1, 1, '2015-03-24', 'Unsafe Like many others, our oven had the front element warp to the point it almost touches the rack. Unsafe and no ercall. Don\'t buy. Onmly lasted a year or so.'),
(7762, 9, 1, 1, '2016-02-26', 'Eight months and kaput! Seems like a great design, and it would be except that it quit working after 8 months.  We really enjoyed features like automatic programming, the large gauge, the push-to-fill lever and a removable reservoir, for easy filling.  But, all of that doesn\'t matter if it won\'t work!  The problem is that the water won\'t move from the reservoir to percolate over the coffee grounds.  Cleaning thoroughly didn\'t help.  After talking to Cuisinart Customer Service I was told that they\'d warrant it but that I\'d have to pay shipping both ways...approximately $35 total.  Alternatively, they offered a 20% discount on a newer model.  I think I\'ll be buying a different brand.  What a disappointment.'),
(7763, 6, 1, 5, '2015-05-01', 'Good looking versatile toaster Performs as expected.  Only time will tell as to how long it will last.'),
(7764, 10, 1, 4, '2015-05-21', 'very happy It came in perfect condition, but it doesn\'t have a lot of power, is kinda weak actually, but for the size it does the job. Very happy with my purchase'),
(7765, 8, 1, 5, '2014-12-23', 'Five Stars Perfect!'),
(7766, 3, 1, 5, '2015-03-21', 'Excellent service! And a great product The first oven I received had a dent.  Applica/Black and Decker replaced it right away!  Excellent service!  And a great product!'),
(7767, 12, 1, 3, '2015-06-09', 'Not great as a toaster This is our second one- after constant use we replaced the first one because it looked bad but it still worked fine. The first one did not toast very well and this one is even worse- bread has to be taken out about halfway through toasting and flipped over to try to get it evenly toasted. The oven part heats food very quickly but at same time food will burn if not checked on frequently. Best thing about this is small size- about the size of a regular toaster so it doesn\'t take up much space on counter.'),
(7768, 3, 1, 5, '2014-08-23', 'Quite nice in the summer when you don\'t want to heat ... Really versatile.  You  an can replace alot of things you use your regular oven for.  Quite nice in the summer when you don\'t want to heat up the house. We\'ve had this or it\'s predecessors for years.'),
(7769, 5, 1, 5, '2015-06-25', 'Great coffee maker This is a great coffee maker, the reservoir is removable with an option for a filter which is nice, because the last coffee maker I owned the reservoir was integrated and the coffee overflowed into it once and that was that. Also the swing out coffee chamber is a good idea as well. I believe it accepts both permanent and paper filters, though I use the paper ones. So far I haven\'t had any issues with it. Makes good tasting coffee and looks nice on my counter. I would definitely get it again.'),
(7770, 5, 1, 5, '2014-03-28', 'Excellent All Around What a great value!  This is the best coffee maker we\'ve ever had.  It is easy to operate, doesn\'t take up too much space, makes hot coffee, pours without dripping, doesn\'t leak when you take the pot out, and looks relatively nice.  The best part was I bought it practically new from Amazon Warehouse and saved a lot of money off the already well priced new unit, though it did have a bit of dent in the front metal panel. We\'ve been using it for almost a year now and it\'s been great.  I did however, break the glass carafe against the granite counter, and the factory replacement cost almost as much as I paid for the whole coffee maker!  Oh well, my fault.  Can\'t really say anything bad about this at all.'),
(7771, 11, 1, 5, '2015-10-17', 'Best kitchen purchase of the year I don\'t know how I lived without this thing. We keep it on the kitchen counter and use it almost daily.  It makes delicious cheese toast and reheats pizza like a dream.  My husband toasts buns for burgers and hot dogs. We wrap the tray in tin foil for easy clean up.  It\'s been so convenient to not warm up the whole entire oven during the summer.  We ordered it over a year ago and haven\'t had a single problem with it.  This would be a great gift for a college student or a wedding gift.  We\'ve purchased a lot of kitchen \"gadgets\" but this is one we definitely don\'t regret.'),
(7772, 12, 1, 5, '2016-02-18', 'Great space saver Love it .  It works great my bagels come out nice and toasty in the oven does the job for  in my case mostly reheating food .  The best part is it\'s a great space saver I have a small kitchen and now I don\'t have to have a toaster and toaster oven .'),
(7773, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'OMG this looks great in my stainless steel kitchen OMG this looks great in my stainless steel kitchen. Didn\'t expect it to look that good for the price i paid ;). not a big fan of single serve so got this instead and love how quickly it brews and you can even select if you like your coffee stronger and not just watery.'),
(7774, 3, 1, 5, '2016-08-07', 'Large oven Great oven. It is one of the only affordable ovens of this size. I recommended to many friends and family members. I owned the previous version and the words near the buttons rubbed out. I hope that does not happen with this new version.'),
(7775, 10, 1, 4, '2015-10-07', 'Not super powerful but works fine for the price! It\'s a decent cheap blender.  Don\'t try one of those crazy kale smoothies or anything but if you have some frozen fruit, yogurt and nut butter you are golden.'),
(7776, 4, 1, 1, '2016-12-30', 'One Star The toaster bell sounds like a smoke detector going off. It\'s loud.'),
(7777, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-01', 'Very happy with my purchase Very happy with my purchase.  Large oven, no need to use the big oven while the A/C is running.'),
(7778, 6, 1, 4, '2014-11-09', 'Four Stars Great roster !!! Inexpensive and work great!!!'),
(7779, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-10', 'Five Stars Good_'),
(7780, 10, 1, 5, '2015-11-14', 'I ordered this for my 17-year-old granddaughter, as she ... I ordered this for my 17-year-old granddaughter, as she is very health conscious, and she loves it for her smoothies after she works out.'),
(7781, 2, 1, 5, '2015-07-11', 'I used this unit regularly for 9 years. Eventually ... I used this unit regularly for 9 years.  Eventually the top heating element went out.  I will gladly purchase this same model again!'),
(7782, 10, 1, 2, '2016-05-15', 'Portable And Compact But Has ATerrible Motor! I had bought this little blender years ago and it didn\'t even last a full year until the motor burned out! Mind you that these are notorious for burning out and regardless of how much you take care of it! I followed the instructions to a t when it came to using mine, I never pulsed for long durations, only short second pulses, I never used big chunks of food or food that was too hard or even ice. The motor is just not strong enough to last unfortunately. I would not purchase this item again due to that reason!'),
(7783, 4, 1, 2, '2015-02-12', 'the perfect toaster - until it broke, TWICE! we got this toaster in 2011 - exactly what we wanted. Then 2 years later the heating element broke. the first time cuisinart sent a replacement one quickly. Then the heating element on that one failed again! and this time they said we had to send it in, and that they\'d look at it, and then maybe send it back after 6-8 weeks. we need a new toaster before that. very sad, would buy it again but it just feels like a toaster oven should last longer.'),
(7784, 5, 1, 1, '2015-12-19', 'Died in about 7 months.  Not heating up anymore. Bought this from Amazon in May of 2015.  It is now December 2015.  This morning I have no coffee.  Did not use it every day during the summer, just on weekends.  But since October used it almost every day.  This morning it won\'t make coffee. Unplugged it, reset the clock, buttons all work and seem to function.  Removed and reseated the water container (a few times).  The heating element must be out or something.  The button works and there is the normal \"click\".  But no heat.  Never left it plugged in all day.  At the most would make 2 pots of coffee in the morning and that was very rarely.  So, it died in about 7 months.  Never had a \"kitchen appliance\" just stop working on me ever.  So, won\'t be buying a Hamilton Beach product ever again.'),
(7785, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-19', 'Excellent coffeemaker I\'m very happy with this coffeemaker. The timer is easy to set and the coffee is very hot and stays hot. I would make this purchase again.'),
(7786, 12, 1, 4, '2016-07-18', 'Four Stars Worked well.'),
(7787, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-22', 'Five Stars It\'s amazing!!'),
(7788, 3, 1, 4, '2014-06-02', 'Meets my needs The expectation was to have a smaller oven that required less energy and was easy to maintain to take the place of a regular oven. Also wanted something that would give off less heat. It met all of those criteria. I have thoroughly enjoyed using it, but one must be careful. It sits on my countertop where nothing is up against it and it has room for air flow because the outside of the oven does get hot enough to burn fingers or perhaps something else. The top could be used as a warming space because it too gives off heat. The buttons are a bit hard to read, but after a bit of squinting and getting the light just right, I could figure them out. I have used this oven for baking meat and brownies -- works beautifully. I\'ve toasted bagels, bread and English muffins and am pleased with the results. Pizza turns out fine. I have not used the convection oven more than once. Clean up so far has been easy other than small bits that fall into the grillwork over the heaters can be impossible to get out, just let it burn off. The removable bottom tray is a great invention and really aids clean up. The door opens down so there is no space in front of the oven to set a plate. Getting foods out can be hazardous and one must be careful not to get burned. The door is quite hot of course and even under the handle. Do not touch anything but the handle and use hot pads. Along with the oven is a metal tray for broiling, grilling, baking, etc. It is quite disappointing. Trying to clean up this tray from grease etc. is a bear. It turns into a gooey mess and will not come off unless you really hit it with scrubbers and elbow grease. The quality of this pan brings down the satisfaction considerably. But I suppose I could buy other pans. I am, overall, quite happy with this addition to my kitchen. I can also see it being useful in a time when we must depend on back up generators or move it to the porch when we are grilling outside to prepare side dishes, etc.'),
(7789, 2, 1, 5, '2015-01-23', 'Five Stars So far so good and looks good on the countertop without taking up a lot of room.'),
(7790, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'K200 Review-Great purchase I just got a Keurig K200 Brewer.  So far we love it.  Heats up water fairly quickly and makes a perfect cup of coffee everytime.  I have used it to make a K-Carafe, K-Pods and reusable filters.  Everytime a perfect cup.  I used to waste so much coffee when making a full carafe with our old coffee maker.  Not anymore.  Best purchase we have ever made.  \"Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(7791, 9, 1, 4, '2016-01-05', 'I love this new coffee maker and gave it 4 stars ... I love this new coffee maker and gave it 4 stars instead of 5 because, 1-it doesn\'t have a temp setting for heater pad and coffee stays extreme hot during the entire time it\'s on and, 2-the gold filter is much smaller than I expected and is flat instead of cone shaped like all my other Cuisinart\'s, so u are limited how strong coffee will be'),
(7792, 10, 1, 2, '2015-08-06', 'don\'t buy this I was pretty disappointed with this product. It has a hard time blending anything.'),
(7793, 2, 1, 5, '2015-03-22', 'Highly recommend Black & Decker for performance I replaced a 15 year-old Black & Decker toaster oven with this model.  Not because the older model wasn\'t working perfectly just recently changed all of our appliances from white to stainless.  Highly recommend Black & Decker for performance, style, and price.  We are slowly getting used to the dial feature to find the perfect toasting time (older model was simple and definitely familiar).'),
(7794, 3, 1, 5, '2015-12-21', 'and am very happy I did We had an older toaster oven that I was very reluctant to replace as it was very small, but more importantly very inaccurate and erratic in the cooking of anything. This Black and Decker oven was very well priced so decided to get it, and am very happy I did! It is very accurate with it\'s temperature and time cooking, and is good size. This was by far the best purchase I made for this holiday shopping spree!'),
(7795, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-21', 'Five Stars Love it. It is a compact coffee maker that does the job.'),
(7796, 11, 1, 5, '2014-08-09', 'Amazing little toaster oven This was an awesome gift I received for my birthday right when our oven bit the dust. I haven\'t done a lot in it personally - a few chicken nuggets for my son here, some toast there, but my husband adores toasting sandwiches in this. It is great because our oven puts out so much heat and it seems silly to use for a small item. The construction is solid and it cleans easily. It also looks really good sitting on the counter.'),
(7797, 9, 1, 2, '2015-09-28', 'Cuisinart Coffee Maker  Single Serving Made great coffee; lasted for about 8 Months, threw it out.  Disappointed to say the least.'),
(7798, 7, 3, 4, '2015-10-16', 'For a single cup it is ok. I have used only twice since I just received it. I used a Kcup and it was fine.'),
(7799, 2, 1, 2, '2015-03-16', 'Must have gotten a dud Pretty disappointed. We bought this to replace our old toaster oven, and have no returned it. It burned the toast even on the lowest setting. We double-checked directions, but could not get it to toast correctly. As an oven, it worked fine; the problem was only with toast. Judging by the reviews, I\'d say we somehow got a dud, but we won\'t be repurchasing.'),
(7800, 3, 1, 4, '2016-08-04', 'Four Stars Ok just received. Not chevked out yet.'),
(7801, 2, 1, 3, '2015-06-30', 'Three Stars small'),
(7802, 10, 1, 2, '2015-03-24', 'sucks Sucks. Not powerful,  smells like burning rubber when you use it.'),
(7803, 10, 1, 5, '2015-10-06', 'Use daily! Have been using it daily for almost 2 years now! Lost lid but my hand covers top just fine!'),
(7804, 2, 1, 2, '2015-10-27', 'Broke after 2 months I bought this four months ago, but only started using it about 2 months ago. I got it to replace a toaster oven I really liked but the timer on that one had stopped working, and it had to be unplugged to turn it off. Anyways, after just under 2 months of use this item completely stopped working. It would not turn on, and the heating element would not do anything. The only reason I am giving this 2 stars is that the warranty will mean that the company will send out a replacement, but I still am incredibly dissatisfied with the product and can only imagine how much landfill volume is taken up with perfectly good looking devices that are made so terribly they don\'t last more than 2 months.'),
(7805, 1, 1, 5, '2016-10-11', 'Five Stars Very easy to use although be ready for constantly refilling the water tank.'),
(7806, 2, 1, 3, '2016-05-15', 'Good, but should toast both sides It works well, but I wish it toasted on both sides at once. There are no toasters on the bottom.'),
(7807, 5, 1, 5, '2016-02-05', 'Fantastic! Way to go, Hamilton Beach! Can\'t say enough about this coffee maker. It sounds like a small thing, but if you\'ve ever tried filling a coffee maker resevoir when your machine is under a cabinet, you know how frustrating that is. This is the answer! It swivels so you never have to pull the coffee maker out! You simply swivel it around and take the water resevoir off to fill it. It\'s brilliant. I think every member of my family bought one, after seeing mine at Christmas!'),
(7808, 5, 1, 1, '2015-07-10', 'I loved it but it died after only 1 month. I loved this coffee machine. It was perfect in every way down to the great tasting coffee and the ease of use. I never have a to tip toe to refill the water or coffee grinds. BUT it does not work anymore after only about a month! I am really sad because I really did enjoy this coffee maker.'),
(7809, 4, 1, 5, '2016-03-03', 'Toasting is perfect. Works real  well as a small substitute oven. Toasting is perfect.'),
(7810, 6, 1, 5, '2015-11-25', 'Five Stars Best toaster I\'ve ever had and I\'ve had a few. Love the temperature controls and the reheat. Very nice.'),
(7811, 6, 1, 4, '2015-07-23', 'Good toaster. Love the way it looks Good toaster.  Love the way it looks.  Only thing ........my toast is not evenly toasted but I can live with it.'),
(7812, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Love the Coffee! The coffee is great every time, and very easy to setup. My only complaint is that we are always refilling the water, so maybe a larger bin would be better. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(7813, 6, 1, 1, '2015-11-11', 'The toaster worked fine for 1 year and 1/2 years We have had this toaster since May of 2015 but it just broke. The inside coils do not get hot anymore so we have to toast our read once and then flip each slice around to toast the other side.  The toaster worked fine for 1 year and 1/2 years. It is too late to return it. Get the two year extended warranty order  a different toaster.'),
(7814, 9, 1, 5, '2015-10-16', 'So far so good. I left my Keurig after many years because ... So far so good. I left my Keurig after many years because I was tired of 1. the k-cup waste, and 2. the stories I kept hearing about mold in the water lines.  I like the idea of no coffee pot. The Cuisinart brews hot and coffee is strong. Other reviews complain about the coffee gauge, but I haven\'t had a problem. It gives you a general idea of how much coffee is left. The only minor issue I have is some of my travel mugs are too big to fit under it, even with the plate removed. But my normal sized travel mugs fit fine. I'),
(7815, 9, 1, 4, '2016-09-18', 'Coffee drinker Awesome coffee machine.'),
(7816, 3, 1, 4, '2016-09-05', 'Best toaster oven we ever had Nice size toaster oven that heats up very quickly. It would have gotten 5 stars but the convection oven fan is noisy. Sounds like it\'s failing even though it is the first time we used the oven on convection.'),
(7817, 12, 1, 5, '2017-01-10', 'Five Stars So happily pleased with toaster oven, so slim on my counter.'),
(7818, 1, 1, 1, '2016-05-19', 'Got a new Keurig Arrived w samples that DON\'T fit ... Got a new Keurig  Arrived w samples that DON\'T fit  Machine rejected them  C\'Mon  Keurig really needs to resize between theeir models?  Meh!!'),
(7819, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-05', 'Five Stars I love this coffee pot. It keeps coffee hot and doesn\'t spill everywhere when pouring.'),
(7820, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-23', 'As good as an oven. Does its job.'),
(7821, 2, 1, 4, '2015-08-30', 'Small characters on panel are sometimes hard to read. ... Small characters on panel are sometimes hard to read. I am not the only one in my house who commented on it. Rather small. capacity'),
(7822, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-15', 'Five Stars Love this coffeemaker.'),
(7823, 12, 1, 5, '2015-05-04', 'Five Stars i love this toaster-oven!'),
(7824, 12, 1, 5, '2015-03-26', 'Five Stars Cute as Wallie'),
(7825, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-13', 'Five Stars Love it! Easy to use and makes good coffee!  I really like the rollers underneath and removable water tank.'),
(7826, 12, 1, 4, '2015-12-23', 'Nice toaster/toaster oven! I really like this toaster/toaster oven.  It seems to have a lot of power.  It is attractive and it saves my counter space.  I would recommend this to anyone looking to save counter space.'),
(7827, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-22', 'It is a great basic toaster I have been using this toaster for some months now. It is a great basic toaster. I would recommend this to others who are looking for a basic toaster without any extra bells and whistles.'),
(7828, 5, 1, 1, '2014-06-02', 'Didn\'t even make it 4 months.  Stopped working two days ago. Made a good cup of coffee but didn\'t last very long at all.  Extremely disappointed with the product.  I would not recommend this product to anyone.'),
(7829, 5, 1, 4, '2015-04-19', 'It works well for now. My last coffee maker ... It works well for now. My last coffee maker worked for one year and one month before it quit.  Time will tell.'),
(7830, 2, 1, 5, '2016-01-24', 'Just the perfect size for a small kitchen or if you want ... Just the perfect size for a small kitchen or if you want to store it in a cupboard.  It toasts bread better than a regular toaster!!'),
(7831, 10, 1, 4, '2015-06-03', 'Four Stars Doesn\'t do as good as my bullet but it\'s pretty good.'),
(7832, 5, 1, 5, '2016-05-03', 'I Love this coffee maker I Love this coffee maker! I am one of those useless-before-coffe people. People in my life, heck, even pets, all know to star way clear of me pre-coffee. This thing is perfect for the lazy or incapable-before-coffee folks! You don\'t even need to go to that hardship of having to fill the pot with water, make it a whole 6 steps across the kitchen, pour the water into the pot (and on the counter/floor/down your nightshirt/whatnot) and into the reservoir. Not only is it super easy to use, but it also makes good coffee. So there it is!'),
(7833, 8, 1, 4, '2015-07-08', 'Four Stars works great for small amounts.'),
(7834, 1, 1, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Keurig is the Best Brewing System The Keurig Brewing System is so awesome that I have purchased two, one for my kitchen and one for my quilting studio.  My guests and I love love love the many choices of pods and flavors.  Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(7835, 5, 1, 1, '2015-12-06', 'Poor product Faceplate fell off both times.(returned one for replacement)  It is made poorly and I will not be buying anything by them ever again.'),
(7836, 5, 1, 1, '2015-04-18', 'Leaks constantly! Although it is a very nice looking coffee maker with the features I was looking for, the pot does not line up with where the coffee comes out, so coffee drips all down the pot and onto the burner underneath, then all over my counter top.  I do get some coffee in the pot, but the clean up is ridiculous.  I\'m not sure if this is just a defect of the one I received, but it is just too frustrating to deal with daily.'),
(7837, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-10', 'We replaced a Kruig coffee make with this Hamilton Beach model because of the reasonable cost and because we can use pods of our choice rather than having to purchase special Kruig pods required by the newer Kruig models. This efficient unit has measured up to its promises. We are very pleased with our purchase!'),
(7838, 1, 1, 4, '2016-08-11', 'Works great most of the time Works great most of the time, keep up on the cleaning and don\'t by the cheap k cups they wont work.  Called Keurig when i had issues, they were super nice and even sent me some replacement cups for my issues.'),
(7839, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-27', 'Five Stars Works great after 2 years and looks in great shape!'),
(7840, 11, 1, 4, '2015-10-17', 'Four Stars Good, solid toaster oven.  I\'ve been using it for a year or so and have no complaints.'),
(7841, 11, 1, 3, '2015-08-11', 'It can keep on heating  so you really have to learn how to use the setting which was not easy  for me. I found it very difficult to figure out how to use it. Once I did it is fine. The 3  stars are because of the difficulty. I had to learn how to shut it off  properly and almost gave it back because I thought it was dangerous. Now I know how to use it and it is OK.'),
(7842, 7, 3, 3, '2015-01-12', 'while I LOVe the concept of using regular coffee or k-cups AND the idea that you can use various size cups, what was unfortunate was that the coffee brewed was just not that good. I\'m not a coffee snob and thought, at first, maybe it was the type of coffee I was using. Sadly, it wasn\'t. On the plus size, it\'s versatile and simple....but on the negative side, just not good brewer. Disappointed.'),
(7843, 3, 1, 1, '2014-05-31', 'Heating Stopped Working I bought this item and used it for about 5 months, then the two top heating elements stopped working. Now I can\'t return it to Amazon and they wont give me replacement parts. So, overall a waste of money. \''),
(7844, 11, 1, 5, '2014-05-26', 'B&D TO1332SBO Toast Oven  (Love it!) Exactly what I was looking for.  I have owned several B&D\'s in the past but this one is definitely my favorite.  Good style and very functional, no issues to date. Please note that I only use the unit for heating up leftovers, baking a potatoe and the toasting function.  Very pleased with my purchase; great service, delivery and price through Amazon!'),
(7845, 7, 3, 1, '2016-08-24', 'I got this machine after another type of coffee maker quit after 3 months. This one never worked right! Never could use pods. Unless I emptied it into the filter! There was nothing there to pierce the pod! Also it took 3 scoops of coffee on the bold setting to get an even marginal cup of coffee and then it had residue in the bottom of the cup! I have worked months on this thing! I finally broke down and bought a Keurig. With the amt of money that was spent on the other 2 makers, I could have gotten the Keurig, saved money and been enjoying my coffee!!! Do not buy!'),
(7846, 2, 1, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Great buy... So far so good . Great for the price..  Would recommend to anyone looking for a toaster oven .'),
(7847, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-11', 'Good value It makes good coffee. That\'s the main thing.  Filling and measuring are easy.  Regardless of the you hand wash or use a dishwasher, the design of the carafe makes it hard to completely empty.  There is a collar that collects water.  Also, the stainless steel front is hard to keep from getting spotted.'),
(7848, 2, 1, 3, '2015-09-07', 'It works well in general but one can\'t select a ... It works well in general but one can\'t select a consistent setting for toasting and so toast can come out too dark or not toasted enough frequently.'),
(7849, 7, 3, 5, '2014-04-10', 'Purchased this item based on features for the price, performs as I had hoped it would. Brews a great tasting cup of coffee. Have had no issues with spillover or leakage, no problems experienced as some of the other reviewers seem to have had. My only dislike is the water capacity, you can only fill the reservoir with 10 ounces of water at a time. I have gotten around this by adding a few more ounces of water and running the brew cycle again to get a full 12 ounce cup full. A minor criticism at best, otherwise I am quite pleased with it\'s performance. The $10 rebate is a nice touch. Highly recommend this unit!'),
(7850, 12, 1, 5, '2016-01-25', 'I absolutely LOVE this toaster oven I absolutely LOVE this toaster oven!!!  It is perfect for my tiny apartment and even tinier kitchen.  It does so many useful things, and it is beyond cheery to look at!'),
(7851, 6, 1, 4, '2015-03-16', 'Four Stars Works well. Bagel occasionally gets stuck but it doesn\'t burn it.'),
(7852, 4, 1, 5, '2015-02-03', 'I love this toaster oven I love this toaster oven. I have used it to toast, broil and bake. It works really well. The only thing I don\'t like is the obnxiously loud BEEP BEEP BEEP BEEP BEEP when toast is done. No way to turn it down either.'),
(7853, 3, 1, 5, '2016-05-10', 'Five Stars works good'),
(7854, 9, 1, 5, '2016-09-23', 'Five Stars Very happy with this product.'),
(7855, 5, 1, 5, '2014-09-22', 'Best Programmable Coffee Maker This is an awesome coffee maker.  Super easy to use and easily programmable.  Some of the reviews mention a plastic-y taste when you first get it... just make sure you follow the cleaning/set up instructions for a vinegar/water solution that gets it to work great from day 1.'),
(7856, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-08', 'Five Stars muy bueno'),
(7857, 7, 3, 4, '2016-10-14', 'The coffee maker works great and much cheaper than a keurig. Only disadvantage is you can\'t use a refillable k-cup as the machine cuts the bottom of the cup on the side instead of punching a hole in the bottom in the center.'),
(7858, 8, 1, 1, '2015-06-09', 'Run from it!! BAD.. Works for only one brew.'),
(7859, 9, 1, 1, '2016-04-24', 'This is because I have been burned by purchases before that are great at first and fall apart 3 months or so ... I waited several months to write a review. This is because I have been burned by purchases before that are great at first and fall apart 3 months or so later. At first glance, this coffee maker is great! It brews hot coffee, apposed to a cheaper coffee maker and all parts are washable. Or, so I thought. The fact is that about 20% of the coffee reservoir cannot be accessed because it is blocked off by a rather silly implemented \"float\" mechanism that is supposed to show you how much is left in the basin. The reality of it is that most people have no need for this. 12 cups makes 4 drinkable cups (and a little more) for myself and wife in the morning with a tiny bit left over. That\'s two coffee mugs each and I don\'t need a gauge to remind me to count to 2. That being said, I rinse out the unit after every use and wash it weekly. It has never alerted me to de-calcify the unit, but I have done that twice since the vinegar solution also does remove some of the coffee off the metal heat transfer plate at the bottom. Last night, the unit started to emmit black flakes that would crumble apart at the touch. I thought it was coffee, and read what others have already mentioned here. I spent 2 hours last night rinsing, using vinegar clean cycle, scrubbing, etc and it didn\'t make a difference. This morning, after spending another 30 minutes at it, I removed the two screws at the bottom (they require a long screw driver shaft) to remove the top section of the basin. This allowed the float unit to slide right out. I was disgusted at what I saw. I quickly got excited as I examined the coffee basin and realized that the coffee maker would work without reinserting the float. Unfortunately, even with the float removed, the black flakes continued to come out. I found that I was able to scrape off the flakes with a wet paper towel and did so for about 20 minutes before I came to a conclusion. This isn\'t coffee. After the coffee residue was removed, the black flakes continued to come off the same spots and had a shiny, glittery quality to them. It almost looks like teflon when it gets scrapped off a pan. I then tried to wipe the interior of the coffee maker - the part that stays mostly dry (with the exception of water getting splashed on the sides) and what do you know. Very slight flaking and plastic strips coming off the side. I did not use the butter knife to scrape it out. I used it to scoop it from the bottom because my hand wouldn\'t fit inside. I HIGHLY do not recommend this coffee maker simply for health reasons. Do a google search and you will that the black flaking problem is not limited to only this particular model but several Cuisinart models. My guess it is either the plastic that is being used or a heat resistant coating that is being used. Either way, even if it is non-toxic, I would never be able to recommend to someone else. At the moment, I am now looking for a completely serviceable machine made from glass and stainless steel where all parts are removable and washable. Even if it\'s something meant for commercial use rather than home use.'),
(7860, 9, 1, 5, '2016-02-09', 'Five Stars My favorite coffee maker ever, but it stopped working after a year and a half.'),
(7861, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-19', 'Also trying to set the timer to get the right amount of time for toasting is terrible. You cannot get the same setting twice Not only is this toaster oven awkward to use, it does not turn off when the door is opened. Also trying to set the timer to get the right amount of time for toasting is terrible. You cannot get the same setting twice. Another bad feature is once you use it as an oven you have to adjust the 2 knobs to get it back to toaster. We have been using this toaster for about 3 months and are looking for another brand.'),
(7862, 9, 1, 5, '2015-05-19', 'We love this coffee pot We love this coffee pot. We have two homes and have one in each. Using this product there is no need. The coffee is hot not and tasty. After using this Cuisinart coffee maker I doubt i will every purchase any other product'),
(7863, 3, 1, 4, '2016-10-13', 'so far so good. we have had this for about a month so far so good. we have had this for about a month.  We had the old version of this previously and that lasted us 7.5 years, for the old model the screen started to crap out and you could partially read the numbers but it continued to work for a long time. we were happy with the old and well see if this lives up.'),
(7864, 4, 1, 1, '2015-09-21', 'Defective heating element, fire hazzard Please read the questions/answers for this item.  Several have posted that the heating element on the right side has warped and bent and is now a fire hazard.  Mine worked great for 2 years, and then this slowly happened, wish I had seen the comments below!  Getting 2 years out of a $25.00 toaster oven would seem reasonable, but I expected more at this price point.  Disappointed in Cuisinart, this is a known hazard and they haven\'t recalled the product.'),
(7865, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-05', 'Five Stars Works great and is a fraction of the cost of a Bullet.'),
(7866, 9, 1, 5, '2015-06-03', 'No more broken carafes!!!! Amazing!!! Best purchase ever!'),
(7867, 1, 1, 4, '2015-06-23', 'Keurig k200 (influenster) So I received this product for free from influenster for trial and review basis only. I was not given any sort of money to write this review. I absolutely love my keurig!! I\'ve always wanted a keurig but never brought myself to buy one and luckily I was one of the chosen ones to test this product out. My box came with the keurig k200 in black, a big box of the green mountain coffee kcups in a variety of different flavors and a small box of 6 coffee varieties as well that also had some tea samples. Then there was a cleanser and descaler bottle, a water filter starter kit, and an insert to be able to brew your own coffee brands. This model has the added benefit of being able to brew larger cup sizes with the additional purchase of a carafe which is not included with the keurig. And without the carafe you can brew sizes from 4oz to 10oz. I must say that I love everything about this product and the only negative I have is not being able to brew the larger cup sizes without the carafe. I didn\'t realize how small of an amount 10oz was. Which I guess means I drink a lot of coffee but it\'s not enough to even fill up most of my coffee travel cups that I have. But besides that, this product is absolutely perfect!'),
(7868, 9, 1, 5, '2016-08-25', 'Coffee-aholic Approved!! Love this coffee pot so much, that this is my second purchase. I researched coffee makers to see if there was a better one out there, and there just wasn\'t. I am a coffee-aholic! I love \'coffee on demand\', and not having that gross pot with the acidic taste of burnt coffee is why I enjoy this coffee maker so much. The first one I bought lasted about 4 years. When I looked to buy it again, it was half the original price, and they made some improvements! It now has an LED display for the clock which really helps! And the removable clear tank on the side is awesome! You used to have to use a pitcher of your own to guesstimate how much water to put in. This is easy and there is no guess work. Love my coffee, and love this coffee maker!.'),
(7869, 6, 1, 1, '2016-05-17', 'Not pleased it lasted almost a year Not pleased it lasted almost a year...burned the toast on low heat. Trashed it and bought a GE...it is nice. We\'re only a family of two and didn\'t  use it everyday.'),
(7870, 7, 3, 5, '2016-01-23', 'Makes fantastic coffee, and uses K-cups or bulk ground coffee. Much easier to use ground coffee in this machine than using the adapter on a Keurig. Love this machine!'),
(7871, 7, 3, 5, '2014-05-19', 'I was impressed with this product, I wasn\'t expecting it to be that quick. I don\'t drink coffee that often, rather I enjoy a cup of tea every once in a while. I couldn\'t justify spending a ridiculous amount of money just to say I own a keurig especially knowing I won\'t use it daily. This product brews a good cup of tea in about 2 minutes. It\'s easy to use and easy to clean. The only complaint I have it that it only brews up to 8oz. Other than that I am completely satisfied with this product.'),
(7872, 8, 1, 5, '2016-08-06', 'Five Stars A great, reliable coffeemaker.'),
(7873, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-27', 'great deal Good deal got it on time .'),
(7874, 6, 1, 2, '2015-12-17', 'Disappointed One side of the bread gets toasted a lot more than the other. And slots seem short. I do like the features it has though (defrost, reheat, bagel). I loved my last Cuisinart toaster, but this one was disappointing.'),
(7875, 6, 1, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Five Stars it turns bread into toast'),
(7876, 12, 1, 4, '2017-01-19', 'Excellent This has been working well.  No issues at all.  I love that it has multiple uses.  I was expecting something a bit larger (and was a little worried it would be as big as I was expecting), but it is smaller than I thought and works quite well.'),
(7877, 2, 1, 3, '2016-06-28', 'Good, but tends to stay on sometimes after you\'ve ... Good, but tends to stay on sometimes after you\'ve turned it off. Could be dangerous if you have kids using it!'),
(7878, 2, 1, 2, '2015-04-19', 'Difficult to control consistency It is difficult to get consistent toast with this because the button that controls the timing of the toast is difficult to get to the exact position; it has to be reset each time. I had an old Black and Decker before and got this toaster largely because I was so satisfied with my old toaster.  The old toaster was much easier to get consistency because you left the knob in the same place and just turned the toaster on.  If it weren\'t for this flaw, I would give the toaster a 4 or possibly a 5 star rating'),
(7879, 5, 1, 5, '2015-10-29', 'Five Stars No problems here. Works as expected.'),
(7880, 5, 1, 5, '2015-03-06', 'The best Very nice and practical design. I dont know why all coffee makers aren\'t made with a detachable water reservoir but not having to use the carafe to pour/spill water into the back of the machine is wonderful. Its good to be able to leave the coffee maker sitting in one position instead of constantly having to turn it around, open it up etc. The door that pops open for you to place coffee and filter inside is also convenient. Buy it.'),
(7881, 7, 3, 5, '2015-08-26', 'I really wasn\'t sure how this would work out. I am not wasting coffee the way I was in the past the coffee is much better. My daughter had bought the Mr.Coffee version which was junk it never worked. This beauty worked great right out of the box I do recommened running 3 or 4 cycles of just water through just to clean out anything left in the manufacturing process. It\'s a solid machine and wonderfully fast too.'),
(7882, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Love this coffee pot Love this coffee pot.  Especially the removable reservoir in the back.  The light is a little too bright for my liking, but a great coffee maker.'),
(7883, 1, 1, 4, '2016-09-25', 'Nothing is perfect Easy to use and meets my need, it\'s not a 5 star because I can easy turn off the machine. The off button on the screen is not easy to press. I find myself unplugging it to turn it off. I now favor the switch on my older Keurig at home.'),
(7884, 7, 3, 1, '2015-07-31', 'This product seemed to work fine the first couple weeks, then it started spewing hot scalding water from the top of the machine. What a disappointment. It was only a couple of months old when I literally had to throw it away. I even purchased the double side Hamilton Beach (Large Pot & Single Serve Combo Unit). That one lasted about 5 months then had to be thrown away, as it was leaking water from the base of the unit. I don\'t drink coffee every day either, maybe 2-3 times a week, so it\'s not like it was being excessively used at a restaurant or something. Hamilton just does not make a good dependable product and one that can stand the test of time. Save your money and get a Keruig or a Mr. Coffee product.'),
(7885, 9, 1, 4, '2015-10-09', 'One of the few carafe-less coffee makers that is not a one-cupper We are on our second DCC-3000 and there are not many options on the market to which to compare this machine. Our first unit just stopped working; this failure followed an electrical storm. We purchased a second unit because we liked the first one so much. About us: We enjoy roasting our own beans and fresh grinding each day\'s coffee. We love the carafe-less coffeemaker concept but not one-at-a-time brew systems. Downsides: This coffeemaker touts a 12 cup capacity but reality is the basket is too shallow to hold the amount of coffee needed to brew 12 cups of medium to strong coffee.  If you like weak coffee, you might, I repeat *might*, get 12 cups out of this.  We found that you\'ll get 10 cups maximum if you use a coarser grind. Putting more coffee in the basket results in grounds spilling over the edge of the filter basket and ending up in the coffee reservoir. These grinds clog up the dispenser spigot which causes coffee to leak out. In this situation, your freshly brewed coffee with continuously leak out of the spigot, fill up the overflow tray, and then spread out all over your lovely kitchen counter. When you come back to get a cup, you\'ll have a mess to clean up.  This is our personal experience because we had to dump the entire reservoir a couple times due to of the leakage problem. Both times, we found grounds in the reservoir and spigot. Lesson learned - don\'t try to get the full 12 cups out of this coffeemaker. Another problem, the gauge. It is inaccurate and just stops working after a while. There may as well not be one. We look forward to Cuisinart (or someone else) coming up with a new model or better design.'),
(7886, 9, 1, 5, '2017-01-08', 'Great coffee maker. I love this coffeemaker.  I got one for my brother and he got one for his cousin.  Big hit in this family.'),
(7887, 7, 3, 4, '2014-05-21', 'This was a great option to the expensive Keurig\'s. Does lose coffee, pods and k-cups. The only downfall is you can not control your serving size (only 8oz), but for the price , you can\'t beat it.'),
(7888, 11, 1, 4, '2015-02-25', 'Great purchase Does a great job toasting and heating food up.'),
(7889, 2, 1, 4, '2016-03-01', 'Four Stars good for the price.'),
(7890, 6, 1, 5, '2016-03-16', 'This has been an awesome toaster - the 3rd one we bought to find ... This has been an awesome toaster - the 3rd one we bought to find one that my husband approved (he is the toast eater in our family)'),
(7891, 1, 1, 5, '2016-05-09', 'It\'s a perfect size because it\'s not as wide as some are We use this for our trailer for camping.  It\'s a perfect size because it\'s not as wide as some are.  We have one at home that is different and I almost bought another one to replace it.'),
(7892, 12, 1, 5, '2015-11-10', 'Perfect little toaster oven It does exactly what it says & doesn\'t take up an entire counter. We recently downsized, while I loved my huge stainless steel convection toaster oven I just didn\'t have room for it. But we weren\'t willing to give up the convenience of a toaster oven for reheating leftovers, & toasting muffins,& scones. This little gem is just right, without taking up too much space. I do like the retro red, but am disappointed the entire unit isn\'t red. I knew that before ordering, just think it would look so much sleeker without the tan top. But 5 stars for functionality, very pleased we chose this.'),
(7893, 8, 1, 1, '2015-08-12', 'Too cheap to be true. Returning. Very poorly made. Water spills all over the kitchen counter and there\'s a terrible burning smell after every brew. I don\'t believe this is a safe product.'),
(7894, 6, 1, 1, '2015-02-23', 'This is no better then my old one This is no better then my old one. It either toasts on one side and burns on the other, or toasts on one side and warms on the other. I really believe Amazon sells factory rejects. But I think you get the idea, It is a lousy toaster. Raymond Ranallo'),
(7895, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Bang for Buck This unit is amazing so far... small, powerful, easy to use, looks great on my counter, and very functional Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(7896, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-18', 'Perfect size for counter top Perfect size for counter top. Avoid heating up the whole house with a Hot Oven, when you can use this little guy to heat small foods up in a shorter amount of time.'),
(7897, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-18', 'Five Stars Really enjoy using'),
(7898, 5, 1, 4, '2015-08-06', 'Great coffee maker but our first one only ran for ... Great coffee maker but our first one only ran for thirty days and totally quit. Had another sent to us about ten days ago so we will see.'),
(7899, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-07', 'After a year, it still works great!!! I don\'t really know what else to say except I am thoroughly pleased with my toaster. I have had it for about a year now and it still works perfect. It toasts the way it should and doesn\'t burn one side while barely toasting the other. I use it all the time to bake too. I bake chicken, fish, roasted garlic. I hardly use my full size oven anymore!'),
(7900, 5, 1, 3, '2016-05-23', 'While I love the coffee machine While I love the coffee machine, I noticed it arrived broken. When you press the right hand side button to open the filter compartment, the top cover for the LCD screens pops right off as well. Apparently it broke (While shipping?) or maybe it was just a faulty product. It works fine, it is just annoying to pop back in every morning.'),
(7901, 8, 1, 5, '2016-04-07', 'Good solid coffee maker This is actually my third Black & Decker coffee maker. I had my first one for 4 years and it died when I moved (I think it may have been dropped) and I got my second one 2 years ago and it works great. This  new one replaces the free one I inherited with my office. It\'s the perfect size for 1 or 2 people. I love that it gives you one set of measurements for the  water and one for the coffee. I actually have saved all the pots from my coffee maker for cooking later and find the Black and Decker spout to be perfect for pouring. I had a kitchenaid once and the spout was not very good as it aged it spilled liquid everywhere. My old pot is still used to make and pour pancake batter though. I love it. I know some people who have had these that don\'t like the type of coffee pot because it isn\'t thermal insulated. I think it\'s personal preference. I think this is a good buy for the price. This is the first time I have shipped a coffee maker and it arrived in good working order. The one thing I\'m a little sad for is the ones I\'ve bought from the store had a basket for the coffee grounds. This one doesn\'t. However this one is cheaper you can buy a basket for the money I saved. I received no discount for my review and the opinions are my own.'),
(7902, 12, 1, 4, '2014-10-22', 'perfect, oven This little oven just fits my needs - size, just right, toast, perfect, oven, better than any I have had.  I highly recommend it!'),
(7903, 9, 1, 5, '2016-03-31', 'To the last drop I waited a year to review this product to see if it held up.  It has been a delight...hope it lasts forever.'),
(7904, 10, 1, 4, '2015-12-06', 'Four Stars It is smelly during squeezing!'),
(7905, 8, 1, 1, '2016-04-27', 'Oscar might like this, because it is garbage. I don\'t think this pot gets hot enough, it makes terrible coffee and gurgles like a monster as it struggles to move water.'),
(7906, 10, 1, 1, '2015-04-19', 'The engine has burned form the first use. Worst blender ever . The engine has burned form the first use. How can I refund the blender ?'),
(7907, 6, 1, 5, '2014-11-16', 'Reliable and Reasonably Priced Great toaster!  Love the multiple setting!'),
(7908, 12, 1, 1, '2016-05-17', 'No timer for an oven. It does not have a timer for oven. It means I need to stand by the oven until it is done. Bad'),
(7909, 6, 1, 5, '2016-10-12', 'Best thing since sliced bread. On time delivery. Wife loves it.'),
(7910, 10, 1, 5, '2015-02-09', 'Works great for my morning smoothie This has taken all guess work out of my morning smoothie. I make the right amount every time and cleanup is super simple. Works well on frozen fruits as well and the price just cant be beat. My first one lasted a year before dying on me, but I was still so satisfied with the product that I ordered another one to replace it.'),
(7911, 5, 1, 1, '2015-06-22', 'Both times I brought in an older coffee maker which worked fine both times My advice is DO NOT BUY THIS COFFEE MAKER!  I received one for Christmas.  It lasted 5 months  and just quit altogether.  After PAYING to have a replacement sent to me, the replacement lasted 3 whole days and quit.  There is nothing wrong with the outlets in my kitchen.  Both times I brought in an older coffee maker which worked fine both times.'),
(7912, 2, 1, 1, '2015-10-04', 'BURN MY TOAST It should be called burn my toast. The timer knob sticks and I have had several things burn, the marking for the knob is also to general. It shows toast half cooked and it burns it if the timer works. DO NOT BUY'),
(7913, 6, 1, 5, '2014-10-30', 'Well made, toasts perfectly. I have the feeling ... Well made, toasts perfectly. I have the feeling this toaster will last me more than a few years. It\'s a keeper. ;)'),
(7914, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-02', 'Five Stars this its a great toaster oven for this price. can\'t do wrong/ good buy.'),
(7915, 10, 1, 5, '2015-01-05', 'This bad boy has lasted me surprisingly long This bad boy has lasted me surprisingly long. I bought it over two years ago and it is still going strong!'),
(7916, 3, 1, 5, '2015-05-01', 'Five Stars great product great people and customer service! THANKS!'),
(7917, 2, 1, 5, '2016-06-22', 'Five Stars My family love it!'),
(7918, 5, 1, 3, '2016-09-12', 'Good while it lasted. Good while it lasted. Started leaking after 1 1/2 years.'),
(7919, 4, 1, 5, '2015-06-06', 'Five Stars This toaster oven is awesome! Looks cool too.'),
(7920, 4, 1, 4, '2015-01-17', 'Just what I needed I am dubious about it\'s prospects for long-term reliability as evidenced by the other reviews here but I love this little machine. Toasts fast; heats evenly; and is so generally useful that I couldn\'t live without it.'),
(7921, 12, 1, 4, '2014-06-27', 'Cute, compact, and a little Complex I like the look of this a lot. It doesn\'t look cheap at all and the style is great. It is very shallow compared to be previous toaster oven, which cuts both ways. On the one hand, I have a lot more counter space now. If you have limited space like me, I think this is great. If you\'re trying to bake personal pizzas...maybe keep looking. Still, I did manage to toast up 2 slices of leftover pizza at once. Finally, I did actually have to read the instructions to understand how the oven portion worked. It wasn\'t difficult but it wasn\'t intuitive either. All in all, still very happy with the purchase.'),
(7922, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-28', 'LOVE IT! Quiet and sure, it WILL take a min or so to heat the water...but its worth the wait.  LOVE IT!'),
(7923, 5, 1, 5, '2015-02-23', 'Love my new coffee pot Love my new coffee pot!  The detachable canister is awesome, no spilling during the fill-up. The coffee basket is so handy, no spilling grounds when filling or emptying.  The coffee is HOT, a feature that is important to me.  Controls and clock are easy to set.  Just the right features for me.  So glad I selected this model.  Great price, rapid shipping as expected from Amazon.'),
(7924, 2, 1, 5, '2015-11-13', 'The best oven there is! The best oven there is! Been using this one for the past 3 months now and it still is in its pristine quality and performance.'),
(7925, 2, 1, 4, '2015-01-21', 'Really Great Value this is a great little device and it is very reasonably priced. it toasts very consistently, and the extent to which it toasts bread is very accurate to what the knob describes it to be. the reason i cannot give this a 5/5 is due to the fact that it has a \"always on\" function which can be very easy to accidentally activate. if you look into the unit and discover your toast has been baked to your satisfaction and twist the knob to \"off\", twisting it even a little too far will result in a constantly activated toaster. not safe. i\'ve walked into my kitchen after 10 min of assuming my toaster is shut off to find it toasting at full speed. other than that, fantastic value.'),
(7926, 10, 1, 1, '2015-12-21', 'Motor burnt out after a week\'s worth of daily use blending frozen berries in milk. I recommend looking elsewhere for a blender. Broke shortly after purchase'),
(7927, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-16', 'Five Stars 1I like mine use for toast the most works well.'),
(7928, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-16', 'toaster I buy the frozen pizza from the store and after putting it in for just about 5-10 min it comes out nice and crispy just the way I like it I will continue to use this toaster to toast my pizza up.'),
(7929, 2, 1, 3, '2016-07-24', 'Ok It does the job but wish the controls were easier to use.'),
(7930, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-10', 'Five Stars Good product. I have been using for a while, and it\'s working great. easy to use.'),
(7931, 4, 1, 2, '2016-10-05', 'strong odor Returned for strong odor when on.'),
(7932, 5, 1, 5, '2015-01-09', 'Good, not burned This product was just as it was described according to the manufacturer as well as most of the reviews. Finally! a coffee pot that doesn\'t drip a drop when pouring! Good, not burned, coffee even two hours after we make a pot. Yay! Love it!'),
(7933, 1, 1, 3, '2015-08-21', 'we like the brewer just wish it heated up faster we like the brewer just wish it heated up faster, found a way around using k cup only pods so all is well, thanks keurig for the free pods for this review. would add screenshot if i knew what that was'),
(7934, 6, 1, 5, '2015-10-13', 'Five Stars good'),
(7935, 2, 1, 2, '2016-02-22', 'Not ergo friendly Bought this mainly for toast and it\'s awful. There\'s no simple on/off switch. Must use the dial to turn for time and then to turn off, but the dial is stiff - very hard for me to turn'),
(7936, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-30', 'Five Stars It toasts'),
(7937, 7, 3, 5, '2016-08-27', 'I\'ve had this unit for about 2 weeks and it has been very good so far. I\'ve brewed 16oz cups with the Regular and Bold selection and they have worked well. I have not had any problem with exploding K Cups. I use the Walmart brand of K cup and have not tried others. I have not yet tried using ground coffee. Some say the machine is noisy. I have no idea where that comes from. The noise level is very low. Like I said so far so good. Only time will tell.'),
(7938, 5, 1, 4, '2015-02-13', 'I like the fact that you can take the water resivour ... This coffee pot was just what I was looking for. I like the fact that you can take the water resivour off to clean it. The controls are simple and easy to use. The only reason I\'m not giving 5 stars is due to the brew time, 10+ minutes for 12 cups. But other than that a great buy!'),
(7939, 5, 1, 1, '2015-09-05', 'died in two weeks. Covered under Amazon warranty, ... died in two weeks. Covered under Amazon warranty, got the second one in June, died in August. For once a day usage I should be refunded the full price. I believe something is wrong in its electronics.'),
(7940, 6, 1, 5, '2014-12-02', 'and does a wonderful job. It is simple, non-electronic, and does a wonderful job.'),
(7941, 5, 1, 5, '2014-11-13', 'Five Stars Great coffee machine. Keeps  coffee hot!'),
(7942, 11, 1, 3, '2015-01-08', 'Not exactly what I was hoping for. Takes way ... Not exactly what I was hoping for. Takes way longer than it should to cook things through. But it does take up little space and saves me from always using the oven.'),
(7943, 10, 1, 5, '2016-03-24', 'easy, effective and fast cleanup this is unbelievable for the price! quick, easy, effective and fast cleanup. i make my smoothies in seconds and just drink it from the cup. mouth piece perfectly fits a straw. great deal overall.'),
(7944, 10, 1, 5, '2015-09-30', 'Five Stars love it, very easy to use and clean'),
(7945, 6, 1, 5, '2014-06-08', 'Cusinart CPT-122 Compact 2-Slice Toaster Great little toaster!  This one replaced a Cuisinart Toaster we used for over 10 years and I believe this one is even better.  Smaller but 2 fat pieces of bread fit - same capacity as our old one.  Simpler controls and more even browning.  So far so good!'),
(7946, 4, 1, 5, '2015-12-21', 'Five Stars k'),
(7947, 11, 1, 5, '2014-09-03', 'Awesome little toaster I don\'t ask much of my toaster. Heat my sandwiches up, and we are good to go. But this brave little toaster is pretty powerful. It\'s definitely a smaller toaster, but I have no problem fitting a pretty decent sized hoagie inside. I am very satisfied with this little guy.'),
(7948, 7, 3, 5, '2016-04-27', 'When the single-serve brewers first came out , I just didn\'t think I would like one. I thought they were priced to high, and the price for the coffee was way more than I could afford , as I am a senior living on fixed income. But, one day while looking online for a coffee maker to replace my old one, on Walmart.com , there it was , jumping off the page, saying try me, Hamilton Beach FlexBrew Single-Serve Coffee Maker. And, at 49.00 ,plus, it had an option ,coffee packs or ground. Needless to say I ordered & in six days it was delivered. To say that I am really enjoying my single server would be understating its true value, in other words, try one , & you will come to acknowledge what I am trying to convey.'),
(7949, 6, 1, 2, '2014-02-17', 'Not GREAT toaster!! Toast will not toast evenly. I you put in one slice it burns one side. Don\'t buy it waste of $$$$'),
(7950, 3, 1, 5, '2016-04-18', 'Love this little oven Love this little oven, heats up quickly, and big enough to cook most meals.  It is much quicker than waiting for our large oven to heat up!  Cooks everything perfectly.  We also have one of these for our outdoor Kitchen, to keep food warm, that come off the BBQ!'),
(7951, 12, 1, 3, '2014-01-30', 'Innovative! I like how it is a toaster and an oven all in one...saves quite a bit of space.  If I purchase again, I will get the 4-slice toaster instead of the 2-slice.'),
(7952, 10, 1, 5, '2015-05-24', 'Great for making shakes This blender works well for making shakes.  I have had it for several months with no problems!  It is super portable and easy to take with me to work.'),
(7953, 12, 1, 2, '2016-11-23', 'The toaster is greater, but the oven is too ... The toaster is greater, but the oven is too small.  I could not fix a whole pie in this toaster oven.'),
(7954, 12, 1, 4, '2014-01-05', 'very handy for the children love this so easy for the teenagers to use like  it a lot for making quick meals when im on the go'),
(7955, 3, 1, 3, '2016-07-12', 'I love that this is so easy to cook in and ... I love that this is so easy to cook in and clean but the put side and top get really hot I almost burn myself.'),
(7956, 5, 1, 5, '2014-06-13', 'Makes that great morning coffee! I have been using this coffee maker for quite some time, and find it to be just what I wanted. I particularly like the button side feature that \"pops\" the basket out; easier to reach and easier to lift out filter. The only thing, but of small importance, that is a negative is that there are small \"wheels\" on the bottom that do not work as well as they should.'),
(7957, 2, 1, 5, '2015-12-29', 'Five Stars Fits on my counter in the space alloted.  Works well.'),
(7958, 11, 1, 1, '2014-07-28', 'One Star toaster was broke when received it so sent it back.'),
(7959, 7, 3, 5, '2016-06-11', 'I wish I would have known the pods came in different sizes.The ones I bought were too large so had to take them back to store.'),
(7960, 8, 1, 5, '2014-05-25', 'Just What I Was Looking For I was in need of a new coffee maker but am sort of limited on counter space. Opted this this little unit and it was exactly what I needed for my morning cup of joe. It makes \"5 cups\" of coffee - which in the real world means it make 3 full mugs of coffee - in about 5 minutes, give or take. As 3 mugs is my limit for the day, the amount is perfect. If you are considering this machine there are three  things you need to be aware of in case you have been spoiled by the bells and whistles found on pricier units - there is no \"pause and pour\" feature, you can\'t program it to start as a certain time and there is no automatic shut-off after a set period of time. You flip it on, wait until it is done brewing before pouring your first cup and it stays on until you turn it off. Just like the 1970s. I have no problem with such a simple, basic machine, but if you want coffee already brewed when you wake up and can\'t remember to turn the machine off before walking out the door, this might not be a good choice for you. But for me it is absolutely perfect. Small footprint, low price, good coffee. I don\'t look for anything else in a coffee maker.'),
(7961, 5, 1, 5, '2014-10-12', 'Five Stars Nice, well designed coffee maker! Love it. Easy to use & great coffee.'),
(7962, 2, 1, 5, '2016-03-28', 'Five Stars works great'),
(7963, 8, 1, 4, '2016-08-30', 'Simple Coffeemaker Works fine, replaced my old Black & Decker coffemaker.  Just wish this had an auto shutoff feature like my old one.'),
(7964, 8, 1, 3, '2015-02-04', 'Replaced by Spectrum - Replacement is better than the original Spectrum brands replaced the coffee maker.  The smell in this one is not nearly as strong, and does not seep into the coffee.  Also, I haven\'t got the problem with the water overflowing the grounds. I have a feeling that the plastic smell is from where it\'s made.  These are not made in USA so be aware! ---Original review--- That chemical odor in the reservoir is BAD.  I hope that over time it will go away, or at least fade.  It tends to throw off the flavor of the coffee. The water runs through it a little too quickly, so sometimes there are grounds in the bottom of the pot.  Also, the basket size is between a 4 and 6 cup size permanent filter, so I bought the smaller of the two, and have to watch the quantity of coffee carefully, or stop the brewing partway through to give the water time to settle through the grounds.  Or I get lots of sediment in my cup.  Yuck. That being said, it does make coffee, and my french press broke.  I\'m going to buy another press and set this aside, just in case it breaks.'),
(7965, 10, 1, 5, '2015-07-30', 'I love it. This blender has helped me make my frozen mocha, and frappe at home. It works well and is not expensive.  I love it.!!!!'),
(7966, 8, 1, 5, '2014-12-01', 'Five Stars i love it a compact size'),
(7967, 4, 1, 1, '2015-06-21', 'Excellent Toaster Oven until heating element tear and warping I am sad to write that like many others, my toaster oven has a problem with the front lower heating element rod.  At first there was a small 1\" long tear in the element casing, but the tear then became two tears.  The tears have grown and now almost the whole element has warped upward and has torn.  And I recently saw sparks coming from the casing split while using the oven that others have written about.  I now think it is not safe to use the toaster oven and will be trying another brand soon.  I appreciate everyone\'s insight on Amazon.  This is a shame, because before this happened, I loved this toaster oven!  Both my husband and I thought this was the best oven we had owned.  I checked my Amazon records and found that I had originally bought this toaster oven in June 2011--exactly 4 years of use.  This puts me past the 3 year warranty period.  Before this toaster oven, another one we had lasted 10+ years.  It is a shame that Cuisinart isn\'t doing more to help customers, even those past the warranty period, with what appears to be a widely known problem.'),
(7968, 11, 1, 1, '2014-02-02', 'Fire hazard I really liked the design, ease of use and sizeof this toaster oven. It was really what i was looking for in this price range. At least until i tried to test it and make some toast. Heavy smoke rolled out the door and i was afraid it would catch on fire. Do not buy!'),
(7969, 11, 1, 2, '2014-08-01', 'Two Stars It\'s much smaller than I thought. I had to revise the review and changed from 3 stars to 2 stars. This one had a problem of toasting bread evenly. Also it doesn\'t fit 4 slices of bread (Wonder Bread might do, but we don\'t eat Wonder Bread.). It is not big enough to bake banana bread either, so that I need to replaced it after 6 months or so. You get what you paid for.'),
(7970, 10, 1, 3, '2015-03-17', 'Gets the job done. Definitely not a premium, durable - performance blender, but it gets the job done. When crushing, ice the motor can cease up and grind a bit sending off a burnt plastic smell -- you Must pulse the blender for ice and thick items or else you will kill the motor very fast (Hold for 2 seconds, pause, Hold for 2 seconds, pause, repeat until crushed). Other than that, it works great for mixing shakes and protein - the blender cup (literally) is very convenient. I can make my shake, pop it off of the blender base and take it with me wherever.'),
(7971, 2, 1, 5, '2015-06-04', 'Awesome This baby can roast a leftover slice of pizza in a couple minutes. Bringing it to a perfect fresh out of the oven taste again in no time. I think microwaving pizza is disgusting and makes it mushy and soft.'),
(7972, 9, 1, 1, '2016-04-11', '... features Pro feature is it has coffee on demand easily Neg feature This machine has many pro and neg features Pro feature is it has coffee on demand easily Neg feature... The coffee reservoir has a spring action plug on the bottom that has broken in mine twice. To fix it I had to buy a new reservoir 2x\'s at a cost of $30 each. Neg feature... The coffee isn\'t brewing properly and the machine stops brewing after only a few minutes. I have to turn it off and on to start the brewing again. I have to do this several times to get the reservoir empty.  I have cleaned the machine several times hoping it would fix the problem but it doesn\'t work. I need a new machine and I am not buying a cuisinart again.'),
(7973, 7, 3, 2, '2016-12-28', 'Slow to make a cup, can\'t fit big mugs under, and makes more of a mess than needed. EVEN when I Measure correct water. Burnt me, doesn\'t pour out all the water sometimes. Doesn\'t pierce the K cups always. JUST SAVE your money!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(7974, 3, 1, 5, '2015-08-03', 'Great Product! It\'s the best toaster oven I\'ve ever bought! Works as advertised. Though I was surprised of how big it was, pleasantly surprised! It did seem to have very little thermal sealing around the corners, but it doesn\'t seem to of made a difference in cooking. Nor does it \"leak\" excess heat.'),
(7975, 1, 1, 1, '2016-02-28', 'Burned plastic, not worth the money. I was so excited to get a single cup Brewer because I am the only person in the house. I was a loyal tassimo customer until the discs became too hard to find. I opened my new machine and did exactly as the instructions told me to do. I went to brew my first cup of coffee and all I could smell was burned plastic. I thought maybe it was just the newness of it. Needless to say, after brewing cup after cup, the taste of plastic never left. I worked on it more. I ran vinegar through it, thoroughly washed every removable part and it still tasted like burned plastic. I returned the piece of junk and now I\'m back to my regular ole coffee pot. I will not be investing in a keurig again.'),
(7976, 7, 3, 5, '2015-10-24', 'I bought this about a month ago after purchasing a Keurig machine online that was described as being \"compact\" but was too big for my condo counter top. This is my first coffee maker of this type and I love it! Coffee is hot and uses Keurig k-cups no problem. It also comes with a basket for ground coffee. Great price, 5 year warranty and looks great on my counter!'),
(7977, 7, 3, 4, '2016-06-01', 'Works very well. I saw some bad reviews on this item but decided to buy it anyway. I\'m glad I did. Just follow the directions and you will have no problems.'),
(7978, 11, 1, 5, '2014-07-01', 'Great little oven Great little oven.  I use it all the time.  The price point is great on this item and I would definately buy another one.  Used it for a few months now.'),
(7979, 6, 1, 5, '2016-10-13', 'Works well and looks good This is a good design and does a dependable consistent job.  Worth the money.'),
(7980, 6, 1, 5, '2016-06-26', 'Not compact but great toast. I ordered this toaster because of the word, \"Compact\" in the name.  I was disappointed when it was delivered.  I don\'t know how they can call it compact because it\'s large!  But it makes the best toast I\'ve ever had, so it stays with me!'),
(7981, 5, 1, 3, '2015-12-13', 'Love the brew and heat selection Have had this quite awhile. We have hard water, so perhaps it is that and I need to clean it more often, but it leaks a bit from the front part of the grounds holder.  Love the brew and heat selection.'),
(7982, 2, 1, 5, '2015-02-21', 'Time for some deluxe grilled cheese sandwiches! We use this often for food and polymer clay. We only wish it were slightly taller.'),
(7983, 4, 1, 1, '2017-01-08', 'bottom element warped and split ... safety hazard We purchased this in May, 2012, and really liked how it worked. This morning while making toast, I noticed the front, bottom element was no longer heating. Then I took a really good look and saw that the heating element was warped and split open (see photos). A quick search revealed that many, many others have had the same experience. If you have this item in your kitchen, throw it away now. It\'s a safety hazard.'),
(7984, 5, 1, 5, '2015-04-06', 'Five Stars Great for the price.'),
(7985, 10, 1, 1, '2015-04-08', 'So disappointed in this product So disappointed in this product, especially the fact that it was made by Hamilton beach. I cut up carrots in small pieces and after blending it there where still a lot of whole pieces left. So not worth it.'),
(7986, 6, 1, 2, '2016-06-23', 'Two Stars Settings never the same ! Don\'t buy'),
(7987, 5, 1, 5, '2014-01-18', 'Just what I needed Well made and easy to use.  I usually only make a couple of cups for my wife and myself, and this is quick and easy. Never drips, and easy to clean.'),
(7988, 9, 1, 5, '2016-06-01', 'Good buy! Great coffee maker!  Looks good on the counter. Quiet. Makes good coffee. Easy to clean.'),
(7989, 11, 1, 2, '2014-07-06', 'but I would not recommend this. You can get s full size one ... Works well but extremely small!!  It would be okay for someone that just needed to reheat something small once in awhile and didn\'t want to take up a lot of space, but I would not recommend this.  You can get s full size one for the same price.'),
(7990, 11, 1, 5, '2014-03-07', 'Wonderful My husband has been wanting a toaster oven for years, and I just never really understood the point. Well, ive been converted since purchasing this. It is beautiful and doesn\'t look ugly on the counter. It heats quickly. Has options to bake, toast, broil and a timer. We had previously been using our oven constantly and it took forever. My husband was so right about a toaster oven, and I was so right about this one! If you are looking for something nice looking for your kitchen, a gift for a college student, etc. I think this is the best choice!'),
(7991, 11, 1, 5, '2015-04-17', '5 Star Toaster Oven ! I purchased this toaster oven as a christmas gift for my boyfriend. We didn\'t want to replace our regular toaster, just have another appliance to cook it. This has been an excellent purchase. Toast, bagels, nuggets, mini frozen pizzas and most everything else comes out great. I was worried that we wouldn\'t get much use out of it since we don\'t eat toast everyday but we have found reasons to use it. I love that that crumb tray comes out so I\'m able to keep it clean on the bottom.'),
(7992, 2, 1, 4, '2016-05-19', 'Have used this for all the heating and baking foods ... Have used this for all the heating and baking foods that are really too small to heat up the big oven.  Works well.'),
(7993, 2, 1, 3, '2016-05-22', 'Three Stars Product is what you would expect'),
(7994, 9, 1, 2, '2015-03-10', 'This is the 3rd coffeemaker like this I have bought This is the 3rd coffeemaker like this I have bought. You would think I would stop but I like the concept of this coffeemaker. The pump broke in two of them and the last one didn\'t keep coffee hot. I went back to an old fashioned percolator.'),
(7995, 6, 1, 1, '2015-10-27', 'Mine Does Not Work Properly. I read such great reviews on this toaster, so I purchased it.  Well, unfortunately, I didn\'t try the toaster out during the 30 day window, so I cannot return it.  For some STRANGE reason, it will only toast on one side of the bread.  Totally weird.  No matter what side I put the bread in, it only toasts one side.  I should have used it when it first came in and I didn\'t. I regret this purchase.'),
(7996, 10, 1, 1, '2015-03-31', 'WEAK Motor burned out within 3 weeks.  Only used it for fruit smoothies.  Super weak.'),
(7997, 6, 1, 1, '2015-09-28', 'bagel setting Bought 7 days ago, bagel setting worked for a few days and now doesn\'t work.'),
(7998, 12, 1, 4, '2017-01-16', 'Four Stars Love this!! Small and compact. I just keep having a problem with the wire rack.'),
(7999, 1, 1, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing System I recently received the Keurig K250 2.0 Brewing System as a gift and I love it. it is easy to use and brews coffee quickly. I definitely recommend this product to anyone looking for an easy-to-use coffee maker. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8000, 12, 1, 5, '2016-07-02', 'Five Stars fits great into my small space. once i got the hang of the toaster oven setting, makes great toast!'),
(8001, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-24', 'I like it I love coffee. I can\'t start my day without it. Dumping the grinds and cleaning the filter of my 4 cup coffee pot several times a day became annoying so the Keurig 2.0 seemed to be the perfect solution. So far I love it. Often I just use it to dispense hot water to make tea (with a tea bag) or cocoa ( I keep a measuring spoon in the can and add 2 tablespoons per 6 oz of water from my Keurig). When I make coffee I use Kcups and find it very easy and much better than dealing with ground coffee. The one thing that annoys me is having to refill the water chamber so often. Once it is a little less than half full I get an error message to refill it, even though there is still enough water in the tank for several more cups of coffee. Overall I am happy with my Keurig. I don\'t think I will ever go back to a standard coffee maker.'),
(8002, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-06', 'Love my Keurig! This is my third Keurig. My last two were mini coffee makers, which I loved, but I decided to upgrade to a Keurig with a water reservoir. This particular coffee maker allows me to make a carafe of coffee or tea, which will be useful when I have guests. One of my favorite things about this brand is that I can choose my favorite color to accessorize my kitchen.'),
(8003, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-27', 'Great buy! Love this Keurig.  I bought the Oasis color, sort of a vintage look.  Coffee is hot, easy to use.  The only slight negative is that it holds 40oz of water, which is not much if you have more than one person making coffee.  It really only holds enough for three cups before refilling water.'),
(8004, 13, 2, 1, '2016-07-27', 'Disapointing I was very excited to receive this keurig as a gift before I leave for college. Tried it out for the first time today and many coffee grounds were found in my cup. Way more then you would expect. And Secondly, the coffee barely got hot! At first i thought this was just because it was new. I ran it a few more times and the same problem kept on happening! are these things cheaply made?? I guess I will have to go back to buying my coffee every morning.'),
(8005, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-16', 'Nice coffee maker I wanted something simple that I could easily brew a cup and take to go- this gets the job done. Looks sleek and doesn\'t take up too much room on the counter. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8006, 13, 2, 4, '2016-02-05', 'No Pearl in my Sand I thought this would be better than the smaller brewer for larger cups. I still have to take the drain tray out to fit my cup under it. It\'s slightly better, but still not great. Brew size only goes up to 10oz. The color is fantastically ugly. Sandy pearl? I don\'t think so- just plain boring ugly tan. There is pearl to it at all. Hate the color so much.'),
(8007, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-25', 'Like the machine but I\'m upset This worked great but now I\'m stuck with all this coffee I can\'t use. Machine won\'t take all the kcups I have all because kurig wants to be greedy.'),
(8008, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-29', 'Smaller footprint Bought this for color and found the surprise of a smaller footprint on counter. Win-Win'),
(8009, 13, 2, 1, '2016-04-18', 'GARBAGE/ DONT WASTE YOUR MONEY I bought this coffee pot and right out of the box it didn\'t work. got an error with the first brew and then spent the next couple of hours trying to clear it. finally I took it back and exchanged it for a new one but wouldn\'t you know it, the new one only worked for a week and I never used Keurig again.'),
(8010, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-23', 'Honestly I like my Keurig... but! The water resevoir and the settings could be improved. Granted, we use ours a lot, so when i need to purchase a new one i will know! As far as settings, they are basic as basic gets. I cant program it to automatically pour 10oz. Its set to 8oz. Which is ok, but thats the other issue.. there is no way that little bit of liquid is 8ounces!'),
(8011, 13, 2, 3, '2016-01-31', 'don\'t like the style Very disappointed in the style of this Keurig. Who designs a water reservoir in the back of the machine. Every time I want to fill the water reservoir I have to pull it out from underneath the cabinet. Wish I would have looked at other models, but liked the price on this one. Also would like a power button on the coffeemaker.'),
(8012, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-10', 'Christmas Present After seeing how much my sister enjoyed using my keurig I thought it\'d be the perfect gift for her when she moved out to go college. I got her the white one and she absolutely loved it. It goes with mostly any kitchen design color. It is so easy to use and brews really good coffees and teas. That being said I\'m gonna go make myself a cup of coffee now :)'),
(8013, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-15', 'Perfect For The Morning Pick Me Up! This is my first keurig and I love it. I use it every day to start off my mornings and it is working great for me. My husband loves it also I can just make him one cup of coffee when he gets home from work. The great thing about this keurig is that it is compact it fits on the counter perfectly in a corner and it has great features and the cup sizes which is great. you can also do tea or even hot coco. This is a great product!'),
(8014, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-10', 'Nice! I use this product daily! We usually have to refill the water chamber at least once daily. We use it to brew coffee, tea, and plain hot water! It has been very easy to use and it\'s polite!'),
(8015, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-31', 'Christmas gift Bought this for my sister and she loves it. She\'s going to school so this is quick and also looks great.'),
(8016, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-16', 'AVID COFFEE ADDICT I love how the 2.0 version looks, it\'s very sleek and modern upgrade. I love coffee and Keurig makes it that much more simple to make your coffee on the go! Setup was a complete breeze! You must get one if you are an everyday coffee drinker.'),
(8017, 13, 2, 3, '2015-11-29', 'Not my favorite keurig system I have two 10oz cups every morning at home. Sometimes more throughout the day. The great is it was cheap with the use of my points and it did brew a good cup of coffee for me. Whats not is my brewer acted up a few times and then died yesterday. 3 months is all i got. I did call customer service which was very helpful and are sending me a new brewer free of charge. I liked the Vue 550 brewer i had before this way better. For whatever reason there is nowhere near the variety of coffee which is why i switched to the Kcup. I hate the waste though. I liked being able to recycle my Vue pods after each use. Drop the Kcup and make all the flavors in the Vue pod. Vue Brewer and coffee was so much better.'),
(8018, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-09', 'VERY DISAPPOINTED!!!!! All the K cups from a previous Keurig do not work in this new one. The box says that they are accepted, but machine says does not accept it. Very disappointed in this machine. Will not purchase another Keurig again. I DO NOT recommend anyone to this machine.'),
(8019, 13, 2, 1, '2016-11-27', 'Disappointed We bought this machine in May and loved it, for about 3 months. Now we have nothing but trouble with it. It leaks, it clogs. We are constantly having to take it apart and clean it. I think this will be our last Keurig.'),
(8020, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-25', 'A very nice upgrade!!! This brewer is an very nice upgrade from our previous Keurig first generation coffee brewer. My wife and I have really enjoyed using this very stylish brewer and even though the temperature of the coffee on the older brewer seemed a tad hotter, the coffee on the 250 is certainly hot enough. We use the brewer every morning without fail and I usually go back for a second cup at 8 ounces although our first cup is always set for stronger at the 10 ounce level. This brewer is very stylish, simple and a joy to use. We look forward to \"cranking it up\" every morning. \"Thanks, Keurig , for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(8021, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-11', 'Keeps this New Mom going! Being a new mother (of a 3 month old), I find it difficult to wake up in the mornings. Little one keeps me up in the middle of the night, and without my morning cup of Java, I dont know how I\'d make it through the day. The Keurig 250 makes this so convenient! No measuring, no waste, no wondering how much coffee or water I need to use, and no long wait while the coffee brews. I just pop the Kcup in, use the touch pad to say what size and strength I want my coffee and everything else is done for me. It\'s ready so quickly and I can get back to Mommy duty in a flash. This is definitely a daily staple in my life!'),
(8022, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-26', 'Keurig 2.0 k475 We received the Brewer and used it on the same day. We were very curious to see how well it works. Our daughters were equally excited so we decided to make some hot chocolate so the whole family could try. My husband washed and ran the hot water before our first brew. It wasn\'t complicated at all and the instructions were all very simple. After that we just put the cup inside and delicious hot chocolate comes out! That simple! At the moment it works great for us, no complaints.'),
(8023, 13, 2, 3, '2015-08-11', 'This was awesome, until it stopped working I purchased this to replace my older Keurig that was starting to get worn out after 3 years of heavy use. This was great right away. I was thrilled with the option to use the larger pods to brew a 14 oz. mug of coffee to take to work. Also, this machine is smarter/more high-tech than the older models. Unfortunately, after a little over a week the machine stopped working and now only brews about half a cup of coffee at a time, with a lot of grounds in it (gross!). I am taking it back today for a replacement and hoping this was an isolated issue. **Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.**'),
(8024, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Love Everything About It It does everything that I expected it to do, and at a great price. I don\'t need fancy lights, or days upon days before I need to refill it. It\'s simple, and if you\'ve never owned a regular coffee maker, you would never even try to use one. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8025, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Love this machine! Use this every morning and at night. Easy to use. Perfect for a single person or a couple.'),
(8026, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-12', 'Love the new colors! Love keurig so and having coffee at your fingertips.'),
(8027, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-11', 'Functional little Keurig So, this Keurig 2.0 is a good little \"starter.\" You can add the carafe later - I found it was available from Keurig, and by using my points it was very affordable. The new machines are all pre-programmed - no way around it. And the K-Cups are all equipped with tiny sensors that are \"read\" by the machine and tell it how much water to use. Yep! You gotta\' use authentic K-Cups with this! No way around that either. However, once you register your unit with Keurig, they do extend a very generous offer on K-Cups. I would not recommend buying this with a Gift Card promotion, because for whatever the amount, it will haunt you like a bad dream if you ever need to return this. And these Keurig coffee makers almost come pre-programmed to break down just when you least expect it. Many, many people attest to this and have to either return it or buy a new one. There are retailers who have unlimited return policies, and it is absolutely worth it for that piece of mind with these most unpredictable machines.'),
(8028, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Great buy This is my first Keurig but even my Mom (avid user) was impressed by this one. I am happy I made the purchase even if it is only for hot chocolate and chai tea.'),
(8029, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-05', 'Not a Happy Camper. Not very happy just got the unit for my birthday and not even a week later having issues. Call the number and the lady was very nice and tried to help. First I told her that this unit has already cost me 7 pods at almost $2 per pod that was around $14 down the drain. And I was not happy. Then she told me I should clean the unit once a week. I told her I would when it came to a week. LOL. I told her I only use the ones with their logo on it to insure it would work and she told me to try too clean it. In short 3 cleans later and over 40oz of H2O and two more pods ($4) they are sending me a new POD holder and a coupon for 1 Free Hot Bev Box/Bag. On the unit I would give about 1 stars. (I did get some coffee out of it. LOL) On the service I would give 4 starts (because I give no one 5 because there is always room to improve.) We will have to see how it goes after the new POD holder.'),
(8030, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Love it! I asked for this as one of my gifts for Christmas, It\'s replacing a smaller older one. I\'ve used it everyday and absolutely love it!'),
(8031, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-10', 'Awesome Product! I use my Keurig every morning and I love how quick and easy it is to use. It\'s a little hard to clean and I winch the cup sizes went higher than 10 oz. but other than that, this machine is great and super reliable!'),
(8032, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-23', 'Love the new look! I love the new look of this Keurig 2.0! The touch screen is very stylish, and I like how the water reservoir is easier to fill up. It\'s a bit harder to put in place now, but I\'m sure I just need to get used to it. This model is a lot more quiet than my older one, and it even has the option for carafe! Very affordable, I love Keurig!'),
(8033, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-07', 'So easy to use! I bought this Keurig for my husband for Father\'s Day and he LOVES it! It\'s very stylish and so easy to use. It\'s compact & doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space. I love not having messy coffee grounds all over the counter like I would from a regular coffee maker. Great value!'),
(8034, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-12', 'Started drinking coffee again I stopped drinking coffee 25 years ago.  Everyone was talking about these Keurig makers, and I got interested in coffee again.  I bought this one in the Oasis color (so lovely).   Now I drink 2 cups of coffee a day!  I usually buy Folger\'s Black Silk.  Love the taste.  I also tried the Pumpkin Spice for the holidays.   My husband doesn\'t drink coffee at all, so it\'s easy to  make one cup without making a full pot.  I even buy coffee from Target online.'),
(8035, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-08', 'very diappointed I am a previous owner of this product, which lasted 15 mos, until it died. Purchased the 200 series on 12/03/15, and it stopped working 12/05/15. Water no longer came out,the small window stopped working. The only thing that worked was the water heated up. I\'m furious w/this product.C'),
(8036, 13, 2, 5, '2016-06-20', 'Love it Bought it for my dad this fathers day. I was afraid at first becuase it didnt work. Its becuase we didn\'t read the instructions. But after we read them we followed the instructions it worked and was so happy. My dad tried his coffee and He loved it.'),
(8037, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-18', 'Love this Keurig.  Easy enough to use I taught my 5 & 7 year old how to make hot chocolate.  I got this at 30% off and paid an excellent price.'),
(8038, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-12', 'A Wonderful coffee machine!! I love my Keurig!! I wish I would have purchase it earlier!!'),
(8039, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-19', 'If You Enjoy Small Cups of Coffee - This Brewer is for You!! I have never had a cup of coffee less than 12 oz. in my life that I can recall. Just made my first cup in this new brewer. Cup sizes range from 4oz to 10oz. Had I known that, I would\'ve never bought this brewer. Don\'t be like me. Do your homework first before you buy. All sizes and all specifications are right here on the Keurig website.'),
(8040, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'So fast Coffee is ready in seconds! No waiting! Amazing upgrade from smaller one cup version!!!'),
(8041, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Christmas present Love it, and I use it every morning. Love the color and it pops my kitchen!'),
(8042, 13, 2, 5, '2016-08-23', 'Great This is a great product.'),
(8043, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-07', 'Love Love Love I\'d been wanting for a while. A long while. Finally Black Friday I bought this thing. (First Black Friday purchase ever, too!) I got the Strawberry, and it\'s adorable. I\'d heard people complain it stays on all the time, and then complain that it has to keep \"preheating\" ... well, if it stays on all the time it doesn\'t. LOL I have not had a single messed up pod, and my mom had some old ones she\'d gotten as samples - and they worked. The only oops message we got was when my son didn\'t close it all the way. I originally wanted the bigger unit, but I bought this one because 1. it was on incredible sale, and 2. I wanted Strawberry. My initial thoughts were \"Well, I don\'t drink THAT much coffee and the smaller reservoir won\'t be that big a problem ... besides all I\'d really be upgrading for would be a color screen and color changing light in the reservoir ........ right?\" I was wrong. Cracks me up how often we\'re refilling the thing. But that just shows how much we love it. It\'s getting a big workout. Bottom line: Keurig, where have you been all my life?'),
(8044, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-02', 'Works Perfectly This machine is great! Does everything I need it to. Great flavor. My only complaint is that I didn\'t get one sooner!'),
(8045, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-01', 'Quietest ever This model is the most quiet of the 4 Keurig machines I\'ve owned.It is also the least expensive as well.The only feature missing is automatic power off.'),
(8046, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-22', 'An amazing brewer for young adults Such a sleek design and its very stylish. Coffee wasn\'t for me until I bought this Keurig K250. It brews tons on K-Cups, very quickly and with a great accurate taste. I always get compliments when guest come over!'),
(8047, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Works great! It brews relatively fast and the drinks are nice and hot. I like that you can choose the intensity of the coffee, and that you can just get hot water for brewing regular tea. This machine replaces my old coffee pot and electric kettle.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8048, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Love! I absolutely adore this new Keurig. I brought this one into my office and love being able to brew a cup whenever I need one. I had an older model that I couldn\'t imagine bringing in to the office as it is larger and clunkier, but this one is sleek and makes my office complete!'),
(8049, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-08', 'College Gal on the Go I got this as a gift for my birthday and I took it off to my college apartment. This brewer is pretty small so i can keep it on the counter in my kitchen and it is so much faster than getting up before my 8:30 class and brewing a full pot of coffee. I am really excited about the strong brewing setting also.'),
(8050, 13, 2, 1, '2016-09-15', 'Not there best Return 1st one 2nd not giving the correct amount of coffee want my old one back what happened to the quality'),
(8051, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-11', 'Throw your old coffee machine away This Keurig was easy to set up. The instructions were clear and it is easy to use. I like how the display screen walks you through everything that you need to do in order to brew your cup. Definitely throwing my old coffee machine away!'),
(8052, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-17', 'very very disappointed I have had a keurig for 4 years. LOVED it, have not had a single problem. I saw the 2.0 came in orange, so I decided to splurge. WORST decision ever! I have literally 70 kcups and I can\'t use any of them! I proceeded to use the samples that came with my new one, and the keurig keeps saying there is a water pressure problem, and to remove the pod. This went on for an hour. I am sending this back and getting another brand, NOT a keurig.'),
(8053, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-03', 'Keurig 2.Amazing! This has been a great lifesaver for us in the mornings and late evenings. My husband loves the fact that he no longer has to make a full thing of coffee while having to waste 75% of it because no one else wants some. I love the hot coca feature especially on our cold nights, it makes the perfect balance. The only negative I really have is that it took a while to set up and also the screen is a little too small for my husbands fingers. The directions were there but I still had a hard time to figuring it out. Other than that, it so easy to use, makes drinks in a jiffy, and I don\'t see us going to a regular coffee pot anytime soon. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods or this review. Love this product so much. Well worth the money.'),
(8054, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-01', 'much better version I like the options and the quiet operation. Additionally, it doesn\'t leave any grinds in my mug. I do wish it had an auto-off feature but not a must have. The water filter is a nice addition. The water tank is expected for the price I paid. Thank, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8055, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-26', 'Easy to maintain and refill I have a Keurig at work. I chose this particular design because it does not have a shiny cup stand that has to be constantly wiped for fingerprints. Also, it\'s easier to refill - the water container comes off easily from the back. I loved the color options and bought the darker red. For my home, it\'s perfect!'),
(8056, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-08', 'Keurig k200 I love this keurig. It is a slim design and beautiful color. The only thing I don\'t like is that you can\'t set this keurig up to turn on/off at certain times. It\'s either always on or always off.'),
(8057, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Great Coffee maker I am enjoying making coffee fast and easy with the Keurig K2.0 brewer. If you are looking for a great coffee maker just go ahead and buy this one.'),
(8058, 13, 2, 2, '2015-07-23', 'Good machine, cup sizes = not very big, Just bought the K200 today because it was on sale at target and it came with a free stainless steel carafe (coffee pot) so i saved $30 there. Kinda wack it only makes 6oz, 8oz, and 10oz pours -- I want my glass filled! 10oz barely filled my cup and I don\'t want to use two kcups.  Pros: makes coffee very quickly with kcups, looks cool. Cons: largest pour is 10oz with kcup.'),
(8059, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-31', 'Business friendly I got the orange colored machine and so far I am content with it. I use it in my office and like the miniature size for conserving space. The larger restoring is also a great perk versus the original mini Brewers. I like the digital display but wish it had a time function so I could set to auto brew like my larger version at home. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8060, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-26', 'Best present for Christmas Gave to my daughter for Christmas. She said it was her favorite present.'),
(8061, 13, 2, 2, '2015-10-23', 'EXTREMELY DISAPPOINTED: Buy an Old One not this one I bought this keurig thinking it was new and wanted to replace an old one. Coffee comes out luke warm and never is hot. In order for me to get a hot cup of coffee I need to put it in the microwave after the Keurig finishes pouring. There is no setting as in older models to change the temperature so I am left microwaving constantly. Absolutely the worst temperature I have ever had a cup of coffee. If I was the only one I would think it\'s me but the 3 people in my family all agree. For a new machine not to have a setting to increase temperature is ridiculous. Called Keurig and they didn\'t do anything. At first I was disgusted about all the kcups I had that I couldn\'t use if that wasn\'t enough my coffee needs to be nuked in order to drink it.'),
(8062, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Love it! We love our new Keurig 2.0 K200 and the ease and convenience of making a single fresh cup of coffee at any time. So simple to use. Wish we would have purchased one sooner. Thanks, Keurig, for the free coffee pods.'),
(8063, 13, 2, 5, '2016-08-26', 'Keurig K 250 Coffee Maker I bought it last November for husband,he has been having a lot  of problems like the  Arm you bring down for to start brewing it.It\'s like you can\'get it to poke hole to brew it why do you want pic.my camera. I am having trouble with it'),
(8064, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-03', 'Great product I really like the Keurig 2.0 250. It\'s small enough to replace where I kept my toaster on the counter. I keep an extra jug of water nearby to it to make it easy to fill up in the morning. I like how quick I can get a fresh cup of coffee. This is great since my husband doesn\'t usually drink coffee and I don\'t want to make a pot for myself in a traditional coffee pot. The iced coffee flavors has gotten him to drink a few cups though.'),
(8065, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-08', 'Variety, Speed, and Good Coffee! I use this brewer to enjoy a hot cup of coffee before I rush off to work and on weekends. It\'s super quick and offers tons of flavors, cup size, and strength options. The only downside is that the K-cups are a bit pricey for single-use and maximum cup size of 10 oz. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8066, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'Great Value Great value, easy to use, works as advertised. The biggest drawback is that there is no auto shutoff after a period of non-use (available on more expensive models). Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8067, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-29', 'Decent cup of coffee Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I am happy with the single cup brewing. However, the size of the carafe compared to how much water it takes to brew seems like a waste of time. Also, the carafe can easily be moved out of the slot which means the entire brew must be started over and the k cup is wasted. For now, I will continue to brew single cups of coffee. I find that one K cup is very strong, so I use the K cup twice to get a larger cup of coffee that is not so strong which creates a more enjoyable hot cup of coffee.'),
(8068, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-29', 'Nice product Ordered the K200 in the color Oasis as a gift for a family member. The color is even prettier than pictured on-line. This model is even quieter than K250 model that we also have. The cup tray slides out easily for larger coffee or travel mugs.  Machine is easy to clean.'),
(8069, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-24', 'Great upgrade from the K10 Mini I bought the K250 at a discount with Club Keurig points. I\'ve had it for a few weeks now and love it. I don\'t drink coffee, but I drink tea nearly every day. I love the reservoir and that I don\'t have to fill it with every cup like the Mini, although the Mini is great, too. I\'ve made hot tea, iced tea, and cocoa. I also like that I can put taller cups under this than the Mini. FYI for any wondering, the min fill line for regular cups is about 2 in from the bottom of the reservoir and is not printed. The one printed on it is the min for a carafe. It will tell you when it needs more water. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8070, 13, 2, 2, '2015-06-15', 'Only recommend if you only buy brand name Keurig Pods i don\'t like this Keurig coffee maker bcz you can\'t use your own pods with your own coffee. Besides that it\'s a nice product. But UN-Happy with the one feature. Will be bringing back to the Store. :('),
(8071, 13, 2, 1, '2017-01-09', 'Must be a LeMon Purchased this coffee maker during December 2016. We use Keurig brand pods exclusively - coffee grounds went everywhere. This gift is going back. Pronto.'),
(8072, 13, 2, 2, '2015-10-15', 'Won\'t make a 10 oz cup of coffee with the K-cup... How do I brew a 10oz cup of coffee from a k-cup??'),
(8073, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Keurig 200: Functional and looks good. Purchased as a replacement for Keurig Vue brewer that died after 18 months. Was not happy with lack of availability of Vue pods and originally chose K45. Output was thin, like water, so returned it in place of K200. Overall satisfied with product (3 weeks old now). Coffee is as planned and it also works with my old Vue pods as well as new 2.0 pods. The water bin is a little smaller than other models, unless you are a power drinker this wont be an issue. Look is sleek and it takes up less space on my counter top. Thanks Keurig for free pods for this review.'),
(8074, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-09', 'Great for daily use, smaller size and looks great I had the Mini Plus brewing system which was working fine for two of us until there was a recall and I was sent an ugly covering for my beautiful machine. So I sucked it up until I saw the K250 2.0 system was released. I got the turquoise as this matches the rest of my small appliances. I like this one more than the Mini because it holds water for at least 3 brewings for us. The color and look of it is amazing. I am really pleased that they came out with this color as I was waiting on it! We brew about 1-2 servings a day and it\'s been nothing but good to us. I prefer this machine over the Mini because it fits many more cup/mug sizes. The only thing I find somewhat annoying is the amount of time it takes to warm the water. For a smaller-sized machine, I expect it to be ready when I turn it on, but I guess my Mini brewer also took time for the water to warm. I also do not like that I can\'t use non K-cup pods since I had a few boxes of pods left over but it\'s no biggie since I still have my old machine. I have purchased but not yet tried the carafe pods. I separately purchased the Keurig 2.0 thermal carafe. Wish this machine would come with one! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8075, 13, 2, 4, '2016-01-13', 'nice unit I am happy I purchased this unit. Works well. I drink 3 cups of coffee a day & reservoir has to be refilled daily. Because I drink so many cups I should have bought a bigger unit. But if you don\'t mind filling often it is a good unit.'),
(8076, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-12', 'Very satified with my purchase When I received my Keurig I couldn\'t wait to open it up . I had purchase the item online and chose the color Oasis and was so surprised how a beautiful the color  was so soft and cool looking which went well with my color scheme in my kitchen.'),
(8077, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-07', 'Would not buy again, next one will not be a Keurig Max cup size with a kcup is 10oz which only fills maybe half of my cup. My old Keurig that just broke would fill the cup. Water resovior is way to small. It seems like we are lucky to get one years use out of any Keurig system we use. I will have to find a way to fix my old since it is much better (when it worked). Keurig is turning into the Apple of coffee manufactures. Next coffee system will not be a Keurig.'),
(8078, 14, 2, 1, '2015-03-13', 'lasted 90 days I bought this model and had been using it to make smoothies, taking the precaution to add finely crushed ice, and avoid overworking the appliance. Alas the blender lasted 3 months. Not much of a bargain, even at the low price.'),
(8079, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-21', 'Favorite way to wake up I absolutely adore the Keurig 2.0 K250! It was so easy to clean, set up, and begin making my first cup of coffee in under 15 minutes! It literally takes 1 minute and roughly 30 seconds to have your own beautiful morning creation to enjoy at home or on-the-go. I only wish that this coffee maker accepted ALL brands other than just those that strictly state they are K-Cups. However, I am happy with the wide selection of K-Cups available online and in-store. Whether you want coffee, tea, hot cocoa, or just a cup of hot water for cooking, this Keurig can do it all. Also, its convenient size makes it perfect for almost any location in the home or office. Solid 9/10!'),
(8080, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Keurig Rocks! This is a great coffee maker. It works flawlessly and the coffee is hot and good. It feels and looks solid. It is stylish (I purchased the new Sandy Pearl color and love it) and it has a small footprint on my counter. I love the mid-size of it. As an aside (but will be of interest to folks) I purchased the Eco-Fill 2.0 and it works in this machine! So, yes, you can brew your own coffee in the Keurig 2.0 k200! I am very happy with my new Keurig!'),
(8081, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-08', 'Bought for my daughter for Christmas and she absolutely loves her Keurig!! Bought for my daughter for Christmas and she absolutely loves her Keurig!!'),
(8082, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-28', 'Highly Recommendable! This Keurig is the perfect coffee machine. This is my first Keurig, and after extensive research, I found it was the perfect one for me. It is small and compact for a single person, but it is so fast, it can brew for multiple people. Plus, it does what all the other size machines do as well. I can brew a small cup of coffee, a travel-size mug for on-the-go, and a carafe so I can share. I\'ve had it for a few weeks already, and I use it everyday. The only thing that can be bothersome (however, it is definitely not a big deal) is filling up the water reservoir every time I brew. But like I said, it does not take away from how amazing this machine is! I absolutely recommend it, especially if you\'re tight on space. I got the Sandy Pearl and it is beautiful! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8083, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Keurig makes my mornings better Love my new Keurig. I didn\'t realize just how simple and easy it was. I will always have a Keurig in my house from now on. The machine is great and I haven\'t had any problems yet, but I wish I had bought a bigger model. I have multiple coffee drinkers in the house and we have to refill it every morning. Sometimes twice. I don\'t really mind and its not really a problem with the machine itself. Just something to consider when choosing which model to buy. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8084, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'My 250 2.0 I am glad I got this product. I make my morning tea and bedtime tea, med-morning coffee, and afternoon iced bev. I don\'t have to fell every time I make a cup. The splatter with the smaller cups, I cured with a stack of coasters, that works great. I always find a way. Love my Keurig 2.0 250.'),
(8085, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-30', 'LOVE IT Use this everyday, multiple times. I love the stainless carafe, choices of K Pods, like that Keurig is going the recycling way too. Orange is awesome, the others colours add flare too. Nice job K from a long time user.'),
(8086, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-30', 'Monopoly Bought the 200 2.0 yesterday to replace our old Keurig because the pump stopped working. Set it up to be ready for Monday morning. I was shocked when I received the Oops message because I did not use a licensed K-cup. I will not play the monopoly game. It is going back tonight after work.'),
(8087, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'So far so good I am new to the keurig family and wanted a compact brewer that can still fit my travel mugs. I purchased the violet color and I love it. So far I am very pleased with my purchase and look forward to many more brewed drinks :) Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8088, 13, 2, 2, '2017-01-18', 'Love the features...HATE the resevoir!! I bought this because of the sleek design & the features.  HOWEVER, I really do not enjoy using this brewer because of the difficult of the water resevoir refill.  I had the design with the resevoir on the side & liked it so much better.  I would gladly pay a bit more for the better design.  I wish it were not too late to return this for a different one.'),
(8089, 14, 2, 3, '2015-12-09', 'Serves a purpose I have only had it a short time. When I made a banana shake, it started to smell hot but worked fine. Only time will tell.'),
(8090, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', '\"Love my new keurig 2.0 K250\" I love having a different coffee every day, and the carafe works great on weekends'),
(8091, 13, 2, 4, '2015-12-28', 'If you\'re familiar with the Keurig Brand, give this a go! I fell in love with the original Keurig, we have one where I work. I ended up with the same Christmas present twice this year so I took one back in exchange for this (they were out of stock of the one we use at work). It\'s not too bad- the cup size was the toughest to figure out.I ended up making a chart of how much water for each cup size. My Dad was skeptical about me getting one since he\'s heard all the bad things about Keurigs going bad but now that he sees what it can do and how easy it is (with the proper knowledge on how to run it), he\'s fallen in love with it. If you\'re familiar with the Keurig machine process then I give it a go. But if you\'re a new-comer to Keurig, I suggest trying one of the more simpler machines that only has 3 brew button options.'),
(8092, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-07', 'keurig 2.0 love the color, great coffee maker!'),
(8093, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-17', 'Great purchase! Love my new keurig!! Works great and the color oasis goes perfect in my kitchen.'),
(8094, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-16', 'Not completely satisfied The Keurig 2.0 250 brewing system is easy to setup and brew a cup of coffee.The Keurig 250 makes a fast and great tasting cup of coffee.The problems I have with the Keurig 250 is the reservoir is small, on some K cups an error message will appear and not brew the Kcup and you cannot use a reusable filter the error message will appear.I wrote this review to receive compensation /free product for my unbiased review.'),
(8095, 13, 2, 2, '2015-07-06', 'Malfunctioned in two weeks Wanted to like product; replaced Vue after it stopped working after 18months. This machine worked for two weeks and then began dispersing coffee at irregular amounts, overfilling cups the last few mornings. (I now have one on standby to collect the liquid so it saves my countertops.) Keurig is sending a replacement, but I lost confidence in the machine already. Moving on to a new brand the next time I need a Unit, and suspect that may be sooner rather than later.'),
(8096, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-13', 'Not HAPPY I just bought the Keurig 2.0 K300 and I am very disappointed in it. I can\'t use any of the other kcups that are not Keurig. and I probably have 3 or more boxes. I will be returning this and go back to my Mr. Coffee Keurig K-cup.'),
(8097, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-26', 'I love this machine! I absolutely love this product. I am beyond happy to own it and can\'t believe I thought about getting it for so long without getting it. I wasted so much money on other, less expensive, brewers that don\'t even come close to this one. I just can\'t put it into enough words. LOVE IT!'),
(8098, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'In love with this coffee maker I recently upgraded my old original Keurig to the K200 and I am in love. The coffee turns out very hot and is made way faster than my old one! The option to choose the size of my mug and the strength of my coffee has been extremely useful and convenient. Buying this Keurig was the best decision! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review'),
(8099, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-31', 'Business friendly I wish that the K250 had a time function for auto brew. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8100, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-27', 'Terrible Terrible Terrible I received my Keurig 2.0 K200 for Christmas. I ran water through it multiple times to get the plastic taste out. The next day it kept occurring and everything tasting disgusting. I went online to see if anyone else has been having the same issue and I wasn\'t the only one. Online it said to run vinegar and water through it and I ran about 3-4 containers through. The smell and taste was finally gone. Well until the next day. I went to make a cup of coffee and it tasted like plastic coffee. Is anyone else having this issue?'),
(8101, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-22', 'HEADLINE: Ryan Braun No Longer Nicole\'s Favorite Brewer This Keurig machine is pretty amazing! I thank the coffee gods for the 10 ounce option and the option to make my coffee \"strong\"--because, I mean, there\'s only one reason for coffee! The machine has a really sleek look and I\'m really excited about also being able to make both single cups and carafes now because sometimes you just need cup number 2 at the same time as cup 1! Also, the machine has a really sleek design that would fit well in any setting. Unfortunately my kitchen is a bit older, but changing out my outdated machine for this one honestly upgraded the feel. The following are my two qualms with my wonderful new machine, which TRULY in no way would outweigh the benefits it offers: 1) It takes a bit longer for this Keurig to turn on and preheat, etc. as compared to my previous one. This is only upon first plugging it in, though, so if you leave it plugged in, you\'re all good. Once the machine is up and running, it works really quickly and despite the various features it offers, it\'s super simple! Secondly (and this may just be caused by my reservations to veer away from exact guidelines), the minimum fill line and maximum fill line seem to be only one 10-oz cup of coffee away from each other. Devil\'s advocate, though, that ensures that you\'re using fresh water for each brew! :) Editor\'s Note: Ryan Braun was not Nicole\'s favorite Brewer, rather the only one she was aware of post-Prince Fielder.'),
(8102, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-14', 'Good little machine We like that this Keurig is available in white, so that it blends into the cabinets/walls in our kitchen. It also takes up a lot less counter space than our old machine. It works great, seems quieter than our old model, and we can use our own pods with it (just make sure that they say they are compatible with the 2.0 series). We also like that we can brew a carafe for company or single cups for us. It also allows for a stronger brew if preferred.  When it arrived, one of the prongs on the water filtration assembly was broken, so it doesn\'t fit perfectly.'),
(8103, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Love this! I love the color! Makes coffee to the perfect temperature! There are 2 things I dislike.. the space between the max and the min water level. After making a 10 oz coffee it\'s at the min level and needs to be released filled. I also wish that it made a larger coffee than 10oz. But overall we love it!'),
(8104, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-04', 'Happy Happy no more wasted coffee in my house. I am absolutely loving our Keurig much less waste and the flavor of the coffee is so much better. My whole family is delighted. Thanks again for the bargain.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8105, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-03', 'LOVE, LOVE, LOVE!!! This is by far my most favorite Keurig model! I purchased this model in the Oasis shade, and I can\'t express how much I LOVE this color!!! I\'m a huge fan of Keurig, so I couldn\'t resist in purchasing this. Beside the color, I love the shape of this model. It doesn\'t take up much counter space, and isn\'t too tall either. The water reservoir is a great size allowing me to make several cups of coffee without having to refill it. I thoroughly love the touch screen they added to this model! It\'s a nice modern upgrade to the older models. It\'s very easy to use, and the instructions are easy to understand. My Keurig shipped quickly, packaging was great, and I\'m very happy with my purchase. I highly recommend this product. I will continue to purchase any Keurig coffee makers from Target since they always stand behind their products making it easy to return or exchange.'),
(8106, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-15', 'I love it I do love this brewer. I had the Keurig mini but wanted a next size brewer with a reservoir. The K250 is perfect for me. The only negative I have is I like my coffee and tea VERY hot/scalding and the K250 makes it hot but not overly. Not a big deal at all. I just nuke it for a few seconds and I\'m good to go. I given a gift as compensation for this review.'),
(8107, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Love it!! I am absolutely in love. Seriously, this is one of the easiest machines to use, even my 8 year old can figure it out. I use my machine everyday and everyday it starts my day off great. I love that in less than a minute I have a cup of hot coffee and it tastes just as good, if not better, than if I went to a local coffee shop. I love that I can choose to make a variety of different drinks with it: coffee, tea and even hot chocolate. This is the perfect machine if you are in a rush in the morning, takes no time to make and it is mess free.'),
(8108, 13, 2, 4, '2016-10-13', 'New Keurig I love my new Keurig K250 as it is easy to use . gives you choice of strength and even mug or pot sizes.  I was disappointed that you can not use any bargain Brand coffee pods that I had from Aldi and had received as a gift.  But the freshness and flavor of my coffee is great!  Customer service has been terrific.  Thanks Keurig for a great product.'),
(8109, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-02', 'I am crazy about this product! I love love love this product! I don\'t actually own it but I am constantly going by my mothers house just to use hers before I go to work. She has the white one and I want the turquoise. Its so fast and easy to brew a cup or 4 at a time. I am notorious for being in a hurry in the mornings and I can easily just swing by and brew a fresh cup. I love all of the k-cup options that are available for it as well! I love this product! I would recommend it over and over!'),
(8110, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-24', 'I just received the new \"strawberry\"color Keurig and it is the perfect red - not too dark - for my newly remodeled kitchen. I would say it\'s like a coral-red. Just stunning.'),
(8111, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Found this at an amazing price I had been waiting to purchase this, until I received an one day only sale and I got it for $50 after all the promotions.  It is a complete steal.  It is so easy to use and so fast.  I have not cleaned yet as I just got it and set it up in the last week.  I absolutely recommend this to anyone that enjoys a cup of coffee/hot chocolate and is always on the go.    I have a 9 month old at home and I have very little time for me in the mornings.  I leave the pod in the night before and while I pack up the car I run it and once everyone is in the car I gab my hot cup of coffee and go.  I absolutely love it.'),
(8112, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-10', 'First Kcup Brewing Machine We have never used a pod brewer before. Extremely pleased with the operation and choices of coffees--also great to offer guest tea and hot chocolate. A little concerned about the construction--mainly plastic; but, we have been careful with use.'),
(8113, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-15', 'AMAZING I Absolutely Love my Keurig. I love all the features and the option to make a 6 cup or 8 cup of coffee. I love that it has a trendy screen. I would recommend a keurig to my friends and family members.'),
(8114, 13, 2, 4, '2015-10-03', 'Does it all I purchased the K200 for my office. It\'s small size fits well on my desk. I prefer this to the Mini Keurig I had previously. This machine has a water tank and with the old machine I had to premeasure the ounces of water. I like the fun colors this machine is available in. I think it makes a great cup of coffee but I find it a tad less hot than my Mini brewer. I do think that the knock off K-cups will have a plastic taste but if you stick to real branded K cups there is no problem.'),
(8115, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-26', 'Love it! I bought this as a gift for my daughter in law, and she loves it!'),
(8116, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Love it easy to use, hot, hot coffee in seconds.'),
(8117, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-03', 'Great so  far! Got it about 2 weeks ago. So far no problems!'),
(8118, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-25', 'Cutest and most efficient. Love it This is as simple as it gets. For those in a rush every morning to get to work, this is the best solution ever. And the variety and flexibility of size...commendable! Great job!'),
(8119, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-16', 'Keurig 2.0 K200 is so awesome! Received this as a wedding gift and is easily one of our favorite wedding gifts! It is slimmer than most of the other Keurigs so it fits very on our counter and doesn\'t take up very much room at all. The options for 4, 6, 8, and 10 oz cups is very convenient and it seems to preheat water very quickly in comparison to other models. The removable water reservoir is also an awesome feature. This is hands down one of the most ballin\' kitchen appliances we have ever owned! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8120, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Best Gift Ever! 100% recommend!  I bought this for my wife on Cyber Monday and got it for only $65.00. I would easily pay the $110.00 for it in store! My wife loves it! It is simple, clean, and keeps us from wasting so much coffee. She is the only one that drinks coffee in the house and used to she would waste half a pot every day because she only drinks one or two cups. Now within seconds and no preparation time she has her full cup of coffee with no waste.  The Design is perfect with it\'s touch screen it is very easy to use. It feels very strong and not cheap like some that feel like they are going to break when you open them. The water is perfectly heated every time and clean is as simple as trashing the pod.  It is now set up on our buffet in the dinning room as a coffee station in the dinning room. All her friends love it too. My buddy is now buying his wife one because we had them over for dinner and everyone was raving about it.'),
(8121, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-28', 'Keurig K250 Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review; however I would highly rate it with or without the free pods. Love the new colors blends in well with my kitchen, allows me to quickly make that cup of tea when I want it, easy to use and maintain.'),
(8122, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Turquoise is beautiful The machine is perfect for me.  I don\'t need a big machine.  The water resivior is smaller than the other ones we purchased.  I love the color.  It makes me happy!'),
(8123, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-15', 'not happy I make 4 cups of coffee every morning and I\'m disappointed that I can\'t brew a carafe of my own coffee.'),
(8124, 13, 2, 5, '2016-05-21', 'More Than a Brewer! This machine has become a nice new companion to me in my room. It looks very nice, the color is silver grey. I need to fill the water tank only once per day. I use it also for tea making, as well as other hot drinks. I noticed the plastic smell in the water, for couple of days. Than it was gone. Keurig will do well to put one of these small odor absorbent packets in the water tank prior to packing. Assembling it and cleaning is also peace of cake. It brews also very fast. Preheating takes about 24 seconds form the time I woke it up from saving mode. Then I hear the sound of boiling water for a brief moment. The brewing process does not take long. I understand it makes certain sounds while brewing which I imagine is normal and is not loud at all. Have I mentioned the light in the water tank, the color is changeable between four different colors w/g/b/r. It looks very cool, especially at night, but it goes off when the machine is in saving mode. I wish Keurig posts a picture of the machine showing its colored lights on the website. I find it to be an excellent machine and more than just a coffee brewer. No wonder Keurig ran out of stock of this model!'),
(8125, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-29', 'Great upgrade! I had to replace my four year old Keurig mini and decided to buy this model.I am very happy I did,because I can use any mug size and the water reserve is great too.The only draw back is that I can\'t use the kcup reusable cups that I have to use my own coffee.However there is such a wide variety of kcup brands that it makes it ok.'),
(8126, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-23', 'The Best Brewer This brewer is by far the most advanced on the market. I was thrilled to see Keurig make alterations to the design to create a sleeker, more compact brewer without sacrificing the amount of storage water (holds 40 ounces of water!!!). This brewer has all the features of Keurig\'s previous brewers without taking up as much counter space! I love that this brewer allows me to choose how strong I would like my beverage to be and has a separate option for brewing hot chocolate. The touch screen is user friendly and makes changing sizes, strength and beverage super easy! Overall fabulous design, I wouldn\'t change a thing!'),
(8127, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Super cute!  Great coffee, and good for smaller areas I got this as a gift to keep in my room.  It fits on my dresser, and I can now make great coffee and hot chocolate without going downstairs.  It also looks great in my room, and matches my color scheme.  I am so glad I got this!'),
(8128, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-27', 'looks complicated but super easy to usr It heats up water really fast but if you want to get clear hot water, do it about 2 times'),
(8129, 13, 2, 1, '2016-06-10', 'i want to love it but i hate it i wish i loved this product. i want to. the convenience of a single cup brewed perfectly is tempting. however, the product has never worked right for me at all. i tried everything, but cups kept blowing up and coffee often shortcupped. now i learned its my water that\'s the problem. I sincerely hope the engineers at keurig get on the problem and fix it with the keurig 3.0 or something, because 2.0 is a big 2.NO! Skip it and get the classic series.'),
(8130, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-14', 'Love! My office purchased a Keurig...I didn\'t understand the hype. When my old school coffee pot decanter cracked, again, I decided to go ahead and splurge on a Keurig. I am so happy I did! I love it! So easy, and I\'m enjoying trying all the different K-Cup varieties.'),
(8131, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-24', 'Easy to use Our keurig is easy to use and stylish! The heat up time isn\'t to long and the coffee always tastes great! The coffee is hot. It was also very easy to set up. P.S. Thanks, keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8132, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-26', 'Great Brewer! My parents have an older Keurig that I hate to use because it takes so long to heat up. I do not have that problem with this brewer, at all! I\'m a college student and this Keurig is great for when I am on my way out the door running late for class! As some other reviewers have said the water tank is a little hard to get on and off but I\'m sure it will get easier with time. I also wish there was a larger clearance underneath where the coffee comes out, sometimes I have troubles fitting my travel mugs under it. I\'m not a fan of the fact that you HAVE to use their special K-cups now, because even some old K-cups that have the Keurig logo on them do not work.I do love that you can select from several different coffee and hot water sizes along with if you want your coffee strong or if you are brewing hot chocolate!'),
(8133, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Loved this! I loved the product! It was easy to set up and use! My grandma figured it out in a snap just following the screen and we both enjoyed a fresh cup of coffee and tea!! Tips for using it: Easy Set up follow the screen! Fill it with as much as water you want, pick the size you like and strength and just brew! How cool is that! It was efficient and great, the only thing I am concerned about is cleaning it. It seems a little complicated to clean but I will just work it out! Overall I love this product and would encourage anyone to get it!'),
(8134, 13, 2, 3, '2015-09-07', 'Works Well But Needs Frequent Maintenance Brewer clogs and/or makes excessively large puncture in pod spilling grounds. This happens often - even right after a thorough cleaning. This is my fifth Keurig brewer but the first to present any kind of problem (and it\'s a replacement for my first B250 brewer that had similar but worse problems. Could there be a design fault in the pod handling mechanism?'),
(8135, 13, 2, 1, '2017-01-03', 'Hate the monopoly game on kcups Got it for a great price, but found out that it requires the kcups for the unit.  Not good.'),
(8136, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Super Kool! I was overly excited when i recieved my Keurig. It arrived on time and with care. It\'s out of the box ready to go. No extra work. Last but not least, its a Beautiful shade of purple! My favorite color! Thanks for being true to your advertisement.'),
(8137, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-22', 'Hello. My Name is Baymax... Yes. I named my Keurig Baymax. Why you may ask? Because he is my personal coffee companion. I fail to see how anyone could fail to see that this is awesome. I use Baymax about 5 times a day. 7 if you count my roomies uses. We are coffee nuts. And this guy is perfect. Sheer perfection.'),
(8138, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-07', 'Love it! I love this coffee maker. I don\'t know why I waited so long to purchase one. Being the only coffee drinker in my house, I love that I can make a fresh cup of coffee anytime. I\'ve always used old style Mr. Coffee maker but this is great and so convenient. I did purchase the My K Cup reusable coffee filter and I love it. I had purchased Dunkin Donut vanilla flavor and tried several ways of making it (different size cup and used the strong method) but I did not like at all. I have not tried other brands of K-cups (Starbucks, etc) but I am happy for now just using the reusable filter. I like a darker richer coffee, much like you get from using a coffee press and when I use the reusable filter, to me, it turns out similar. Very happy with my purchase!'),
(8139, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-29', 'My orange beauty I am so very happy I was able to find a K250 in my favorite color, orang!!  I adore it!!  And it\'s features are a big plus, of course!!'),
(8140, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Coffee lovers This is my first Keurig and I must say...I am in LOVE! Setup was easy. The screen tells you everything you need to know to operate it. It\'s quick and efficient. Never would I have imagined that I would find a brewer that I absolutely love. Early mornings are made easier with just the touch of a button.'),
(8141, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-26', 'Awesome product!! This sleek design for the Keurig is awesome for any kitchen! It holds 40 oz. of water and you can brew so many different flavor coffees! So happy with my new Keurig!'),
(8142, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Best keurig Great Kuerig, gets water hot instantly. Makes the best coffee and hot cocoa super fast. Definitely worth it and stylish, love that it comes in variety of colors.'),
(8143, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-26', 'First Keurig I\'ve ever owned! This is my first Keurig I\'ve owned and I LOVE it! It is so easy to use. It doesn\'t take up a lot of counterspace either! It makes the perfect cup. I\'ve been missing out and I\'m so glad I have one!!'),
(8144, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-29', 'Fast brew, flexible brew size, looks great I like the machine - it looks great and works great. As a steady drinker of at minimum 16oz of coffee in the morning with a spouse that drinks the same it doesn\'t look like it will ever be our daily brewer (without the additional purchase of a carafe). Awesome option of brewing into a carafe - maybe we need to cut our coffee consumption back :)'),
(8145, 14, 2, 3, '2014-07-24', 'crushes ice Crushed ice for a drink. The High Low settings are too confusing - as they have been on these things for years. And you have to hit off to reset. Very light weight and does not fit under the cabinets on the counter.'),
(8146, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'coffee yeah I bought 2 of these this year from Target, my girls loved them.'),
(8147, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-26', 'Compact I love how the water storage has been moved to the back  and with the new Keurig comes a water filter that you replace every two months! Love it!'),
(8148, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-28', 'Love my Keurig! I love this product! I have owned other Keurigs but this is my favorite! I love the different size options for the coffee and the option for the carafe. It is a perfect size for the little amount of counter space that I have. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8149, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-25', 'very happy with Keurig purchase! morning, and evening, enjoy the variety of great tasting coffees. The machine works flawlessly if you follow the simple instructions to maintain the machine. I have owned mine since spring.'),
(8150, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-12', 'Perfect Home Brewer Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8151, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-04', 'DO NOT BUY!!!! the product is bad don\'t buy it. it does not even brew the right amount of coffee don\'t buy it its not worth it'),
(8152, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-19', 'Very Good Single Serve Brew System - even after reading revs I waited to write a review until I had my Keurig for several weeks to compare performance against the many reviews that already existed (especially the negative ones). Pros: First, the system is everything I needed in general for brewing a single serve cup of coffee - nice and hot, plenty strong. I enjoy the flexibility of different flavors with every cup. It is easy to use, actually stores on my counter under the wall cupboards with enough space to lift the lid to place in the cups. Having a variety pack of the regular coffee and teas has been wonderful for guests who all have differences in opinion for which coffee/tea to have, and although more expensive than knock off brands, not out of line for single serve coffee preps (especially when ordering in more of bulk size number of cups). Since I am one who orders gourmet beans for flavored coffees using an online service, I am anticipating the release of the My KCup for this model. Cons: Most of the things I didn\'t like are not deal breakers, but more wish list vs. general functionality. A better staying and easier to replace water reservoir lid (easy to misalign and fall into reservoir), drip tray not attached to unit is too easy to move. One too many screens for access for dispensing water. Too long a time until auto shutoff of the unit (for my type of usage, which is typically morning and evening only - not all day use). Comments vs. other negative reviews: 1) I did not need a \"to go\" carafe cup size and did not order this product expecting it to do so as the specs for brewing were provided. 2) After washing my carafe before use, I did not experience the \"smell\" that others have. 3) I have never experienced grounds coming through the system. 4) I have not experienced any program or power issues with this unit as were described in other reviews - and the water dispensed is hot enough to burn! Suggestions to Keurig: A larger reservoir would be nice, but as a single cup user this could lead to microbial issues. 2) Programmable for specific user preferences would be nice since there is more than one user in our household. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8153, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Keurig Is Love I use the Keurig when I need an extra boost. I like the fact that I can have a delicious cup of coffee so quickly and have many flavor options to choose from.'),
(8154, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-14', 'most excellent coffee! looks great, works great easy to use, tastes good.'),
(8155, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-27', 'Cutest Keurig When I saw this Keurig in the Oasis color at my target I HAD to have it!! The color really pops and I am always asked where I purchased it. This has become my favorite coffee maker as I use it every morning and often in the afternoons too! It\'s extremely convenient and makes a delicious cup of coffee. This is a must have for coffee lovers!'),
(8156, 13, 2, 2, '2015-09-28', 'Extremely Disappointed I purchased the Keurig 2.0 and am Extremely Disappointed that it does not brew a 12oz cup using a regular Kcup. The ad states it brews a 4oz to 30 oz which is only true if you are using special kcups for the mug and carafe. The older Keurig that I owned was capable of brewing a 12 oz cup. Wish I still had my old one. I am returning the Keurig. In addition, you have to keep setting the cup size to a 10 oz each time you brew a cup. You cannot program it to stay on the 10oz brew size. Very poor technology.'),
(8157, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-13', 'Great Brewing System This Keurig system is amazing! It\'s easy to use, looks great on your counter tops, accommodate any K brews you can think of! You can\'t go wrong with this baby!'),
(8158, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Coffee/ tea maker. Got the Sandy pearl color. Looks fabulous in our new kitchen. Easy to use and doesn\'t take up too much space. Nice that you have option of one cup or carafe. Price was good.'),
(8159, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'My New Keurig! I love my Keurig! As a busy college student, it is absolutely perfect for those long nights studying or when you just need a little pick me up. I cannot wait to try more k-cups. I love the various size options for those days you just want a taste or when you want more. The options are endless. I bought mine in black to match my other kitchen items but I also loved all the fun colors you could choose from! I also love that it holds more water than some of the other Keurigs so I do not need to worry about filling it up as often. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8160, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-13', 'Awesome Keurig I have really enjoyed this Keurig. I had an older model before and this is really easy to use.'),
(8161, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-22', 'So Convenient! I was meaning to purchase one for awhile now and so glad that I was able to get my hands on one now! This is such a convenient machine, especially for my husband and I who can get by sharing a cup of coffee a day. We definitely don\'t need a whole pot of coffee and this allows us to easily make just a cup whenever we want without excess. I love that it brews so quickly and is available in multiple sizes suited to your needs (4,6,8, 10) and it\'s nice to have the option of getting carafe for it if we decide we want to be able to brew a larger amount. It\'s also nice to have the \"strong\" option for brewing and I really love that I can now make a variety of hot beverages, including tea in this machine and use the \"hot water\" option for other hot water needs! I do wish that it had the capability to brew a little hotter but for the convenience and all the other benefits it comes with, I don\'t mind that too much. Some people are unhappy that it rejects K-cups from other companies but being new to the Keurig that doesn\'t bother me right now and after looking into it, it seems there\'s easy ways to get around this. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8162, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Great Coffee Maker K-250 We enjoy good coffee and start our day together having a morning cup before work. We talked about getting a Keurig and finally made the decision to purchase the K200 Series, K250. We absolutely love it and the variety of K-cup options available to us. It is so easy to use and looks wonderful on the counter. No mess, no more counting the scoops of coffee - it is really simple to use. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I received compensation / free product for my unbiased review.'),
(8163, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-22', 'Update? Downgrade? I bought this in the light blue (oasis) color to update my K75 keurig. Even though my old machine still works wonderful, I thought, it\'s a good deal, why not update it to match my cute new kitchenaid mixer? Well, first thing that bothered me taking it out of the box was how cheap this one feels. The bottom tray is light and cheap feeling vs the metal one on my older model. The reservoir where the water goes is apparently so sensitive. I had distilled bottle water poured in there, which apparently it didn\'t like because it wouldn\'t set the sensor off, so it kept telling me to \"add water please\" until I dumped out my bottled water and put in sink water. (Our sink water doesn\'t taste so fancy, but it made it work.) Well then as it chugged along and brewed my coffee, it was a splashy mess. I mean I get it, but there was so much that splashed it was like, for real? Maybe if I had a black one, whatever I could get away with cleaning it whenever, but the light blue color shows it all. And who wants to wash off their keurig after every cup? My old one didnt do this. The water reservoir is awkward. I have it under my cabinets on a pod storage stand thing, but the tank is in the back where it\'s awkward to pull it out and fill it up. It\'s like I gotta move the whole thing to get water in it. And the whole top lid comes off, vs my older model, it\'s just an uncomfortable shape. Also doesnt snap on or feel secure. Just kind of sits on top.  I had to refill it after one brew. Compared to my older model, I thought itd be nice to have a more \"slim\" one, but its really not even much smaller. It takes up the same amount of space, if not more because you gotta move the whole thing just to get water in it. The screen is user friendly and easy to understand, but unless I cant figure it out, it doesnt have a clock to tell you the time? Overall, I would spend the few more dollars and get the bigger model. My parents have that one, so I thought this one would compare but nah. At the end of the day, it brews coffee, what it\'s supposed to do, but it\'s cheapy feeling for a \"nice\" coffee maker. It\'s a cute color, and is very pretty. But we like coffee in my house and although it\'s an \"update\", it feels more like a downgrade everywhere else wise.'),
(8164, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-31', 'Keurig 2.0 - Not the same quality as the first Keurigs I bought this Keurig at Christmas time, loved the color Teal and it matched my kitchen perfectly. My old Keurig was almost 3 years old so I thought it was time for an upgrade. BIG mistake. I started getting the \'Brew interrupted, needle under pressure\' error message after a couple of weeks of use, but would be ok after I went through the whole cleaning process. Then it started happening more frequently, then daily. So I called the 888 number. Customer service was great after I explained that I did everything Google told me to do to fix the problem. The good news was they\'d send me a new one out, bad news no Teal. No biggie. Receive a Pearl White one and very first time using it, get the same error. Go through the whole cleaning process and still ERROR. So I call again, they\'d said they\'d send another Pearl White one. I got it yesterday and it was Black AND second cup of coffee, SAME ERROR MESSAGE and coffee grounds in my coffee. So now what?????'),
(8165, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Very Pleased This Keurig is affordable, sleek, function, & makes great coffee! I strongly suggest it.'),
(8166, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-16', 'Love this product! I absolutely love this product! I\'m always on the go so grabbing a quick cup of tea before I head out isn\'t an issue. It\'s very easy to use. Just fill up the container with water, put in your k-cup, press the button, and your drink is ready in less than a minute! The only con I have is that it only fits k-cups made for Keurig 2.0 machines. Other than that, awesome product and I highly recommend it!'),
(8167, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-19', '3rd machine and still no coffee This is my first time qith Keurig...bought first machine and it said brew interupted...the customer service associate decide after troubleshooting it was defecting. I went and returned the machine...2 machine same thing...one hour of troubleshooting later...they are sending me out a new one. Just got my new Keurig today and guess what..same problem...they are giving me free boxes of pods for my trouble which is great!! If I could use them?? I now have to wait until Monday for corporate to call me...horrible first experience..'),
(8168, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-07', 'Love! This is my first Keurig and so far I love it. I had a Hamilton Beach one cup maker right before this and so far the Keurig is wiping the floor with it. Lets hope it keeps up the good work.'),
(8169, 13, 2, 1, '2015-08-07', 'AWFUL@ Do yourself a favor and please do not purchase this product. I purchased my initial brewer in June and am now going to be on my 3rd...yes third brewer. It seems as if the brewer works for about 3-4 weeks and then it completely stops functioning. I called customer service this morning, and although both workers I spoke to over the last two months were polite; I was told that the best they could do was send me a new brewer. The warranty for a cash refund is thirty days from the point of original purchase. I am tired of this machine and having to waste my valuable time talking to customer service, wasting k cups, and spending time at FedEx (you have to send pack a part within 30 days in order to be offered the free replacement.) I was understanding when this happened the first time, but now I am beyond frustrated. How can you not offer me a cash refund when you have already had to ship me two replacements? What does that tell you about the quality of the product? I saw some questionable reviews before I purchased this product, and if I could go back, I would have listened. I had always been a fan of Keurig and had the Vue in the past. Never again.'),
(8170, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-01', 'Convenient - great for brewing a cup at a time I love the brewer - it\'s the right size for my countertop and it consistently brews a great cup of coffee. My only problem is that there isn\'t any way to turn it off without unplugging the power cord. I brew a cup every morning; I don\'t want or need the brewer to keep water preheated 24 hours a day. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8171, 14, 2, 5, '2015-12-31', 'Superb purchase selection!!! The item I have has done great performance with all 12 speeds!!! No cleaning hassles and dishwasher savvy!!!'),
(8172, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-09', 'Love the smaller size of the machine! I\'ve always loved Keurigs since the first time I used one, but I was hesitant to purchase because I don\'t have a lot of counter space. The K250 is perfect! The smaller water tank makes the unit much slimmer and I can squeeze it back in a corner of the counter. I actually like the small tank better because it forces me to use fresh water. And the color is fantastic! Every morning when I look at the turquoise machine, it makes me even happier than I already am to get my delicious, fresh cup of coffee. Though it can brew the carafe-sized pods, it does not come with an actual carafe, so this keeps the cost down. And I love the settings on the 2.0 system that allow for a 4 oz, 6 oz, 8 oz, or 10 oz brew, and you can even select to brew it \"strong.\" The quality of the brewed coffee is great. I use a reusable pod with a local coffee that I grind myself, so no wasteful plastic pods filling up a landfill. Definitely a happy customer, and I would recommend this product to any coffee drinker! *Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8173, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Works greaT, coffe taste great I have had my K2.0 for about a month. Love the way it works and love the coffee it makes. I\'m happy. Pleas note: \"Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review\" That said, it is a great addition to our kitchen'),
(8174, 13, 2, 2, '2015-11-28', 'Will not take ALL K-Cups I bought this as a wedding gift to my son along with about 10 boxes of tea/coffee. He had to bring me back almost 1/2 the boxes because they will not work in the new machine? that makes no sense especially since i bought off the Keurig website. not good all at'),
(8175, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-01', 'So disappointed with Keurig I usually do not read reviews...not ever, but since getting the larger 2.0 & realizing I could not use the filter to enjoy my own favorite coffee ( although that has recently changed), I now understand the importance of reading reviews. I was going to purchase the 2.0/200 for weekday use, only to find out I can\'t use my ole pods....that really sticks....... Shame on you Keurig!!!!!.......from a faithful customer who has owned your brewer since the very first one. With each new brewer comes new disappointments. Instead of improving the brewers, Keurig just seems to come up ways to stick it to the consumer. I do believe it\'s probably time to change over to another brewing system by another company........because I refuse to stop drinking coffee!!!!!'),
(8176, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-01', 'Very Poor Quality This was the second one I purchased in a matter of only 6 weeks. It would barely, if anything even dispense the selected oz\'s and would be continuously \"pre-heating\" and when you would press start it would still take 3+ minutes to brew the the little that would come out.'),
(8177, 14, 2, 5, '2014-12-25', 'Man what a beautiful blender n works marvelous thank you Simple to open n use immediately'),
(8178, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-01', 'Makes our mornings better! Thank the heavens for this new Keurig design! We absolutely love the Carafe option! It\'s brilliant we can make a whole lot of coffee as well as keep the option of doing individual cups. The best of both worlds. Another thing that I like about it is the Water tank is bigger so I don\'t have to fill it up as often. Over all this machine is great. Oh and the descaling solution is such an awesome plus!'),
(8179, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'Keurig Keurig for the win!! Thanks target for a great deal and a great product'),
(8180, 14, 2, 4, '2015-12-09', 'I like I likes it so much!!!!'),
(8181, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-19', 'It\'s pretty good Great for making a cup here and there. It won\'t replace my current maker. I will use both. Super quick and easy. Great color, lol'),
(8182, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Great Upgrade to our coffee! Decided to upgrade our original Keurig to the new 2.0 system. Love that we now can brew a carafe of coffee. Also live the digital screen and multiple options for each cup. Plus it comes in multiple colors so we were able to pick on that really pops on our counter.'),
(8183, 13, 2, 1, '2016-04-14', 'Worst 2.0 I purchased the 2.0, after have 2 other Keurig\'s coffee makers, but this kept stop working or turning on by itself. I called in the Customer service line twice, they told me what to do, it worked for a couple of weeks, and finally had to throw it in the garbage. I love the Keurig\'s simple coffee maker, but unfortunately when you made it a bit more complicated, it just wasnt working. I just wish I could have been able to return it for an exchange for something different.'),
(8184, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Love it! This Keurig is smart and Stylish! Everything I never thought that I could have in a coffee maker! It is so easy to use and as a college student I am very busy, and the fast pods make it easy to brew and go! Thank you Keurig!'),
(8185, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-11', 'HUGE DISAPPOINTMENT I am extremely disappointed with the new Keurig 2.0. It will NOT accept any of my old coffee pods that my previous Keurig did. I am disappointed the Keurig would make their customers buy their brand of coffee in order to be able to use the machine. I cannot return this machine to the store where I purchased it so I will be trashing it and buying another brand machine that will accept any manufacturer K cups. I loved my previous Keurig and was excited to get this one for Christmas. What a disappointment to find out I have an entire drawer full of flavored coffee\'s (sorry Keurig, not your brand) that won\'t work. Will never buy another Keurig again and have posted to my FB for all my friends to not buy one either for this reason.'),
(8186, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-04', 'Replacement Keurig Bought this to replace an older larger model keurig we had that was taking up way too much space. We were glad this one is quite smaller, and that we can adjust the strength of our coffee {we like our coffee strong around here}. Another pro it tells you before you start brewing if water is needed to be added. (our old model did not do this we would set coffee to brew , come back to find it never brewed because it needed more water but did not tell us this in the first place) The only downside to this model is that it only takes certain k-cups and doesn\'t take a MyCup insert. So I am now stuck with leftover pods from my last brewer that aren\'t compatible and bags of coffee I cannot use either. Otherwise, this Keurig works perfectly fine for day to day use and am quite pleased with it. *Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!!*'),
(8187, 13, 2, 4, '2016-02-16', 'It\'s not that bad of a machine so far I recieved this as gift for christmas and I love it. Haven\'t ran into no serious problems with the machine. But I do know I don\'t waste as much as coffee now like in the past with my regular coffee machine, by making to much coffee and throwing it out, or by just wanting 2 or 3 cups \"not a full pot\" and making it the worst 2 to 3 cups of coffee so it gets dumped out \" more waste\" . Yes, the pods can be expensive look around you can get deals on the pods. I\'ve spent $5 on a box of pods not to be bad, just look around. And for your regular coffee thats where our carafe comes in and we use it. It all up to you to make it costly or not.'),
(8188, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-21', 'We love our Keurig! I purchased the Keurig mainly for my fiance since I don\'t drink coffee but then found out there are so many other drinks you can make in the Keurig too. We uses it for coffee, iced tea, lemonade, hot chocolate, and whatever else we could want. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8189, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-27', 'Because one cup is not enough!!! I have always wanted a Keurig and I finally got one!! I absolutely LOVE mine!! I brew 2-4 cups of coffee a day and its a breeze. I also am loving the fact that I can instantly make tea for my kids and not have to deal with a hot mug from the microwave. This machine is elegant and sleek and looks wonderful on my counter! I can\'t wait to get a storage drawer to match!'),
(8190, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Oasis Mint Color I have a larger Keurig for my home and wanted a second one for our RV and this is just perfect. When I saw this color, I just had to have it. Makes a perfect cup of coffee every single time.'),
(8191, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-08', 'Love it The best thing about the keurig is that you dont waste coffee. Compared to the normal coffee makers you dont have the option to make either a single cup or a pot. I love my Keriug.'),
(8192, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-17', 'Absolutely love it! I got this Keruig 2.0 for a Christmas present and I absolutely love it. I was playing around with it this morning and found more settings when I took away the tray part and realized I could brew up to 14 oz and there is also a froth feature. I can\'t wait to try the froth feature. It also allows me to use non Keruig brand kcups which I like! I will definitely not go back to my old one if I need a replacement down the road.'),
(8193, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-29', 'It makes a mean cup of joe! The size is great! It doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space and it\'s modern and sleek. I like that I can brew a cup at different amounts. The water tank is a bit awkward to fill directly and then replace, so I fill a pitcher full of water and pour it into the tank. I also wish the carafe wasn\'t so expensive. Otherwise, I would use this coffee make everyday. Looking forward to trying new flavors of pods! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8194, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-19', 'Just wowed When I first got it, I added water to the max fill line so it could clean, I waited a few minutes and it kept saying \"add more water\" which I did and then when I cleaned it out, all of sudden it started preheating. The instructions said it\'ll take 3 minutes to preheat but his one took more than what it said.'),
(8195, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-21', 'BEST PRICE ANYWHERE AND LIGHTENING FAST SHIPPING! I ordered this Keurig coffee maker to give to a friend for Christmas.  Target had the BEST price anywhere I had looked by at least $20, I also got free shipping.  It was mid December when I ordered it online and I wasn\'t sure if I\'d get it in time because I\'d waited so long to order.   I couldn\'t believe it - without choosing overnight shipping - I ordered on a Friday and it was here on Monday!  I have this model of Kuerig and I love it.  Obviously I\'d recommend it to a friend since I bought one for a friend!  :)'),
(8196, 14, 2, 1, '2014-10-13', 'Don\'t bother! I did not find this blender functional at all. It takes a lot of time and effort before it actually chops up ingredients. I constantly had to stop it and push the items down and add more water. I will be investing a little more money to get the job done!'),
(8197, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-19', 'AMAZING This has to be the best coffee machine I have ever invested in. My daughter had been telling me to buy it for a while and finally, I caved in when our old coffee machine broke. It was an amazing deal and it\'s an amazing product. It\'s fast and the coffee is perfection each time! i strongly recommend this product to any and all coffee lovers. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8198, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Looks great I haven\'t used it yet bc I don\'t close on my house for about another month BUT I took it out the box and it looks great! I can\'t wait to use it. Its sleek and stylish and the color beautiful. I bought the pearl color. I bought it to replace my keurig mini which is the 1st model that came out. I can only use certain size cups for that one. I\'m so excited to use my bigger coffee mugs to start my day!'),
(8199, 13, 2, 1, '2016-06-16', 'Constant problem!! This is my 4th Keurig in less than a year. I finally decided to try the cheaper 2.0 250 model and for the first couple of months it worked great! Then, even with using the cleaning tool, we continued to get the message \"contents under pressure, etc. etc. very annoying, especially when you\'ve cleaned it 5 minutes previously!!!! I called customer service and said they would call me back within 24 hours! Red flag here!! I went to read reviews on the 250 model. Guess what? You can\'t read any reviews! On any models!!! Another red flag that tells me this company is in big trouble!! Will update if customer service indeed, calls me back!'),
(8200, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'Kerrie 2.0 K200 We love our new Keurig!!!  The ordering process was easy and the price was fantastic!'),
(8201, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-10', 'Finally bought a Keurig This is the model that I\'ve been waiting for. Smaller footprint, but more useful than the single cup model. I think it\'s right for the person who drinks 1-2 cups. I purchased on sale plus received a Target gift card that I put toward purchase of ss carafe, so I was happy! Strawberry red is great color. Be advised that non-Kuerig k-cups really do NOT work in this machine. Easy to learn & operate. Glad I bought it.'),
(8202, 13, 2, 5, '2016-11-24', 'sATISFACTION good quality and great price.'),
(8203, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-11', 'Awesome Brewer! This is my first Keurig and I must say...I am in LOVE! Setup was easy. The screen tells you everything you need to know to operate it. It\'s quick and efficient. Never would I have imagined that I would find a brewer that I absolutely love. Early mornings are made easier with just the touch of a button.'),
(8204, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-13', 'Great theory, can\'t get it to work Received a Keurig 250 for Christmas. It worked OK for a few cups then started to receive \"Incomplete brew\" and a cup full of grounds. Keurig sent replacement coffee pods but the problems continued, a new Keurig 2.0 was sent, same problems, new pod holder, same problems, a second replacement Keurig 2.0, same problems, now they are sending another replacement pod holder?? I\'m ready to throw it in the garbage.'),
(8205, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-21', 'Keurig 2.0 FAIL We gave a review before indicating how you cannot brew more than 10oz, well we called customer service as it indicated on our feedback and was told we need to buy the VUE pods which will brew more ounces. We go out of our way to find these VUE pods as we were instructed, spent $13 for a box, put one into our 2.0 and get the \"oops this pod does not work with this system.\" Seriously Keurig, you do NOT know your own machines. We are over the new Keurig systems and gonna let people know it is a waste of time and money. My husband is super upset at we had had to go thru, twice and the system is a big FAIL!!'),
(8206, 13, 2, 3, '2016-09-28', 'Disappointed compared to previous brewers! I am disappointed that I need to press the Keurig kcup and puncture the bottom before I close the handle. If not, they leak all over the brewer and I need to take it apart and clean it. With all of my previous brewers, I just popped the Keurig kcup in and lowered the handle without a problem.'),
(8207, 13, 2, 4, '2016-01-26', 'Replacement for Mini Single-Cup Recall I use the brewer in my Office for guests and myself. It\'s very fast and efficient.'),
(8208, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'I love the new K250! It even comes in my favorite color! I purchased this Keurig because I was first introduced to the Keurig family during my internship, the machine make coffee \"making\" fun and simple. Pop in your favorite coffee pod and wait for no more than a minute and have a fresh, perfect cup of coffee prepared for you. I love my new K250 Keurig and the best part, it\'s in my favorite color!! As a college student a simple yet fun item is a must have in your dorm or even in your parent\'s kitchen when you\'re living at home. I cannot picture my life without my Keurig and I love that it makes K-Carafe sizes, my maker came with a free K-Carafe as an offer for purchasing it, and I couldn\'t be happier. I can\'t get enough about telling my friends and family members to purchase a Keurig, even if it\'s not this particular size, you can never go wrong with any Keurig you purchase! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8209, 13, 2, 1, '2015-06-04', 'The concept is good but...... the machine forces you to use Keurig products only. You cannot use any other k-cups. It also does not pour full cups. We may have just gotten a lemon, but was very disappointed with being forced to use only Keurig products.'),
(8210, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-30', 'Love it!! I have gone back and forth on whether to get one or not. Finally decided to get one. I live with my sister and she mocked me a little. Now I can\'t keep her away from it. Every time I get a new flavor, she wants to try it. And I can\'t keep the regular Folger\'s in stock. She keeps drinking it all. We have a regular coffee pot. And we use the Keurig every day.'),
(8211, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-17', 'Wouldn\'t buy 2.0 I\'m receiving a second 2.0 to replace the first, which was a lemon. I\'m hoping it\'s not the whole version. Our old Keurig was a workhorse. Our new 2.0 immediately started clogging, spitting out grounds and not working, even after cleaning. We had it less than a month before it started having issues, and we only use it for 6-7 cups a week.'),
(8212, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-17', 'Why no refillable pod for the carafe? I\'m REALLY disappointed that there is no refillable coffee filter (pod) made for the carafe size. It\'s so bad for the environment to keep producing the k-cups and filling up the earth with plastic. PLEASE consider producing the filter for the carafe.'),
(8213, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-27', 'horrible! I got the keurig 2.0 k200 for Christmas since my older keurig wouldnt work anymore and I\'ve hated this keurig since day 1! My coffee has all the coffee grounds in my cup every time! I called keurig for help and was told that it was the k-kups I was using (keurig brewed ones). So they gave me a code for 2 boxes of k- kups and I thought i would give it a try. I still end up with a whole cup of coffee with all the grounds in it. I\'ve tried cleaning the machine with vinegar, using the silicone bulb to clean the needle and nothing has helped! No one wants to help fix the problem just blame it on other things. It seems these coffee makers are built for quantity NOT QUALITY anymore, very disappointed!!'),
(8214, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-17', 'Love it! I love my new Keurig that I recently received as a gift to replace my old one I had for 5 yrs.'),
(8215, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-31', 'Great Coffee Maker Great product, my only concerns are there is no way to recycle the cups after the machine uses it and the large size of the machine. You really have to have a lot of counter space available to use it.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8216, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-07', 'VERY DISAPPOINTED I do like the slim design and the choice of colors. However, I am extremely disappointed that the system advertised 9 brew sizes but in fact only brews 4-,6-, 8- or 10 oz. sizes. I have 14 oz travel mugs and I have to brew 2 times to get a full mug. My coffee mugs are all large and again I have to brew 2 times to get a full mug of coffee or 3 times to get a full mug for tea as the hot water only brews 4 or 6 oz sizes. Who drinks only 4 or 6 oz of tea??? I also do not like the fact that I cannot use a reusable pod. I miss my custom blends of the seasons and my freshly ground beans. I wish I never spent the money on this. I am going to resurrect my old one - I haven\'t tossed it yet - and it still brewed better than this model. EXTREMELY DISAPPOINTED KEURIG! It\'s not even worth shipping back to you.'),
(8217, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-01', 'Does not use Vue Pods as advertised on this site I had many Vue pods left when that machine died (and Keurig would not replace it) and I tried to use them in this machine since the site said it would brew them - however they did not and got an error. Ended up throwing away many good pods because of that.'),
(8218, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'I love my keurig!!!! I bought for myself because it saves me from making a whole pot of coffee and wasting it..this is truly more than what i expected..fast delivery as well..'),
(8219, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-29', 'K cup coffee maker I love the color and it is great!  First one of these I\'ve ever bought. I\'d buy another!'),
(8220, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-19', 'Water pressure problems In January I bought the 2.0 200 model. It worked great for about a week. Then the second week it started giving error messages and wouldn\'t brew the coffee. I spoke to the company and they suggested exchanging it at the store I purchased it. I did so. I have only had the second one for one week before getting the same message. \"Water under pressure\" when I carefully open it and remove the pod and close the machine, hot water spits out everywhere. I only use Their brand cups and only make one cup a day. I spoke to the company again. They walked me through three \"repair/ maintenance\" procedures. It still doesn\'t work. I will be returning this for a full refund. After being up all night with a little one, the last thing I want to do is fight with the coffee maker and be on only for 45 minutes with keurig. These new ones are awful! I have no idea what I am going to buy, but it will not be a Keurig. (Was a loyal customer for almost 6 years).'),
(8221, 13, 2, 2, '2016-05-27', 'Poor product I purchased my first k200 a year ago - it stopped brewing 6 months later.  Because it was within the warranty, Keurig shipped me a replacement.  I get the \"brew interrupted\" message about twice a week (I use it everyday).  This requires me to clean the needle and then restart the machine.  After which, the machine does not brew the correct size.  What a pain!!  This machine is supposed to be about convenience, which it is not AT ALL!!  I miss my non-2.0 machine which was much more reliable.'),
(8222, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'Love it!!!!!!!!! I use this unit to make iced tea, it is great!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8223, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-05', 'First time Keurig User We had a regular coffee maker for years, so when we finally had the chance to try out the Keurig we did. I really love the size, and it works fast. It\'s a perfect fit in our home, since everyone has a different taste in drinks. Since there\'s so many varieties no one has any complaints.'),
(8224, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-27', 'Love It This is my first keurig, and I\'ve fallen in love! My husband and I both love coffee and this Keurig makes it all so easy! Love the touch screen and the option to brew strong coffee. I would and have already recommended this to all my family!'),
(8225, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'Love it! I am a college student who doesn\'t have money to spend on outside coffee shops. For a while I was spending a great amount of money on coffee, money that I did not have. I decided to do some research on Keurigs. The K200 series caught my attention, it was small, cute and affordable. I really like that I was able to choose from different colors. Overall I use it as well as my mom. She and I both love how convenient and fast it is. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8226, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-30', 'Great little brewer I have owned (and still own) several different Keurig brewers. I bought the K250 for a holiday home I was visiting. It was perfect for making our morning coffee and I didn\'t miss the larger reservoir or the extra features of the higher level brewers at all. If you kitchen counter space is limited, this might be better for you than the larger and mor full featured brewers and the mini plus (which has no reservoir)'),
(8227, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'perfect We bought this for my grandfather and he loves it - very easy to use.'),
(8228, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Love My New Keurig I love my new machine though its size took some getting use to since I was upgrading from an old 4-cup drip machine. I love it\'s fun color (turquoise). I love the flexibility of having hot coffee, hot water, or other hot or cold beverages from one machine so everyone gets a cup of exactly what they want without delay.'),
(8229, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-02', 'Great little Keurig! This is a great coffee maker recieved as a gift from my grandchildren. It\'s handy to make a cup of coffee, but I\'m disappointed that some pods won\'t work and it won\'t accept a reusable filter. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8230, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-28', 'Slightly less features than previous my previous model I was upgrading from my old Keurig thinking that this was more sleek, newer and had more features. I was slightly disappointed that this is missing a few features that my old Keurig had. Mostly the ability to set a timer and have it turn on by itself in the morning and also the temperature adjustment.  I also was under the impression that it came with a Carafe. It does not. I guess I should have read the fine print. It does show one in the pictures describing it though. And it\'s not exactly cheap. About $30. Considering that\'s almost half of what I paid for the Keurig itself, that\'s quite a bit.  Overall good product, but I would say this is a simpler model.'),
(8231, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-05', 'Yummy coffee! I\'ve always wanted a keurig ever since My roommate got one for Christmas. I bought a cheep knock off one, but it doesn\'t even compare! The coffee is smooth and rich, not grainy and too strong. The downside about the product is it\'s a little too fancy for me. It\'s not a bad thing, but I think having a touch screen on a coffee maker is a bit extreme.'),
(8232, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-28', 'Update of an old favorite Like the older models, this Keurig is fast, convenient, and virtually mess-free. I love the touch screen, making my drinks more customizable with the \"strong\" option for coffee and the increased variety in ounces. However, my one issue with it was that it only accepts K-cups produced after a certain date (since a year or two ago). For this reason, all the K-cups I had bought from a while ago were unable to be used. All in all, the product itself is a good quality item and makes the mornings a little better everyday.'),
(8233, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Love it! I bought this for my 14 & 11 yr old nieces to make hot chocolate, cappuccino, and etc. The Oasis color is very pretty and it is so easy to use! Needless to say, I am now the coolest Aunt!'),
(8234, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'Another Great Machine, Love It! I\'m a long time user and have had many Keurig machines over the years. This model is the best bang for the buck so far and truly enjoy using it every day.'),
(8235, 13, 2, 4, '2016-11-02', 'Good new colorful option I bought this because my old Keurig needed replacing. Love the color options and allows brew choice (strong coffee, hot chocolate, tea or just dispensing hot water). It feels like I need to refill the water more often and it will take in a lot of water when preheating. Also, I can\'t figure out how to turn it off so I end up just unplugging it (a digital on button and does not describe on/off in the manual). Overall the color and ease of a Keurig makes me overlook the other stuff.'),
(8236, 14, 2, 5, '2014-04-28', 'Great for smoothies Just got this blender at Target (it had been out for a few week). I\'ve only used it a few times so far but its been making wonderful breakfast smoothies.'),
(8237, 13, 2, 1, '2017-01-01', 'EXPLODED! VERY DANGEROUS!!! We use it for a while with no issues until I came home one evening and found it exploding on its very own! I unplugged it but when it was plugged back in it went right back to exploding on its own! Shooting hot water & coffee grounds everywhere!! I worried about my own safety and the safety of my young children. Beautiful color! (Light aqua)'),
(8238, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Fast, efficient coffee maker I bought this because it was a great sale, with a $15 gift card included.  It works great & was a good buy!'),
(8239, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-13', 'Keurig it is! This item is pretty good, i had no problems with it, was worried about the kcups restricted usage but nope its good, just follow the instructions and enjoy the coffee you always wanted...'),
(8240, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'Great price and easy to use! This brewer is much better than the older model I have which is the single cup brewer that is now over four years old. The water will heat up first so when you do put the k-cup in and hit brew, the coffee will be made right away. The only issue I have with this brewer is the fact that it doesn\'t brew EVERY k-cup I have. If it doesn\'t clearly state \"Keurig\" around the outside of the k-cup, it will not work in this brewer. You will get a message on the display reading \"Oops...this cup will not work in this brewer.\" Luckily I still have the other brewer and put those cups in that one. Keurig does give you the option of sending them in and they will replace those k-cups, but I\'d rather just use them up with the other brewer. Overall I\'m very happy with my purchase! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8241, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-01', 'I love the colors! I love this Keurig, I have had other Keurig brewers in the past and had a good experience, what led me to purchase this one was that I loved the color... I love that it can brew the carafe size pods, down side is that you have to make sure you buy the new Keurig k-cups... I had to give away some of the older style ones because they could not be read. The coffee is good and hot, I love the different sizes, one more feature I would\'ve like to have seen would have been an auto-off feature as my last one had that. Over all, I am very pleased. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review'),
(8242, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-04', 'Perfect Edition To The Kitchen! I love how I can brew my favorite coffee/tea while getting ready in the morning. It\'s a great edition to the kitchen and the variety of colors let me pick something that matches my appliances! Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(8243, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-21', 'Way Better than the Original! I love this keurig! I had the original brewer (which i loved) but it was so big and clunky. The size of this brewer is wonderful, not to mention it doesn\'t humm loudly like the old one did. Also the touch screen is pretty cool looking! Only complaint is that this brewer requires that you use only Keurig K Cups, so that means no ground coffee in the reusable cup. I personally don\'t mind it as I always buy Starbucks K Cups, but I can see it being an issue for the coffee drinker on a budget.'),
(8244, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-13', 'First Keurig A little bit lacking in the instructions on how to use..eg doesn\'t tell you to put in the water filter first..had read online comments so knew that.Very easy to set up and use.Easily wiped down.Heats up quickly.A little noisier than i thought,but quieter than a kettle heating up and a lot faster.Have used numerous K-cups in in.No problems at all. Keurig gave an awesome welcome gift too.Very well packed..'),
(8245, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-06', 'Love my keurig!!! Pretty design and easy to use. Recommend it to anyone. Very easy to use and easy clean up. Would buy another one if I had to!!!!!'),
(8246, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-01', 'Very Easy to Use I use this product everyday, I never have to wait for the machine to heat up whenever it\'s plugged in. I love the fact that it\'s so small and can fit on my counter along side my other appliances.The quality of the coffee is great, I would definitely recommend this product to my friends.'),
(8247, 13, 2, 1, '2016-07-27', 'I have bought 3 Kerrigan k200 I love drinking hot coffee, so I bought 1 like my daughters and set it up. Well it would not take my mountain green 1/2 calf coffee kcups. I tried all k cups it kept pouring coffee grounds in the cup. I had to buy another one. And again I put this time the Duncan donut coffee kcups and the half calf green mountain. Well I went and got a third one thinking something had to be wrong . Well I have the 3rd one in its place and it will take a Duncan donut cup one time and then it will spew coffee grounds the next., I love drinking coffee at my daughters but I am unable to drink it in my kitchen. So disapointed.'),
(8248, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-15', 'Keurig 2.0 K250 <33333 I love this Keurig! I\'ve never gotten one before, and this was the perfect one for me. It\'s quick, easy and tasty. It does exactly what a Keurig is supposed to do. No more, no less. I love the reservoir and easy clean-up of a Keurig, and that at the push of a button I can smell coffee through my apartment. I\'m a college student and it\'s perfect for lazy, old me. Highly recommend!'),
(8249, 13, 2, 1, '2016-08-20', 'Don\'t buy I use cups that say Keurig and get an error message that they aren\'t compatible.  Machine stopped working after 3 months...called customer service and was told you need some orange disc to clean it once a week.  After 3 Keurigs in 3 years, we\'re switching to a drip coffee maker.'),
(8250, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-28', 'Love Love Love! I love this coffee machine! I use at least once a day for coffee. It\'s fast and efficient, great for those of us that are in a hurry in the mornings!! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review!!'),
(8251, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-14', 'All That and a Bag of Coffee Beans I used my Keurig today for the first time and I love it. I have one of the older versions of a Keurig and that one works well, but this one is awesome. The best feature would have to be the touch screen. I mean does it get any better than that? It\'s pretty cool. I love how it also can make up to 4 cups of coffee. I\'ve always used just my regular coffee maker to make more than one cup of coffee. Now, it\'s convenient that Keurig has come out with this product. It also makes the coffee a lot quicker. The machine is silent when brewing which is nice. Another plus is that you can fill it with a lot more water than previous Keurigs and you can stick a water filter in there. Overall, I definitely recommend the Keurig 2.0 K250 for those interested in a great, fast and easy coffee maker.'),
(8252, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'I love my Keurig brewer! I set up the brewer this morning and used it for the first time and I\'m very impressed with it! Set up was easy and brewing was quick. The coffee tasted delicious. The unit is great-looking as it sits on the kitchen counter. The lcd screen is easy to navigate. What\'s so great is that you have the speed of making a cup of instant coffee (!) with the quality and taste of a fine brew. Highly recommended! P.S. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8253, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-07', 'LOVE MY NEW KEURIG! I BOUGHT MY KEURIG FOR MYSELF FOR CHRISTMAS AND LOVE IT! I BOUGHT THE TURQUOISE ONE AND IT BRIGHTENS UP MY KITCHEN!'),
(8254, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Best Coffee Machine I bought this specifically for me to use in college. I\'m pretty sure I\'m going to need all the caffeine since I\'ll be lacking sleep. Love the variety cup sizes i can choose from and the types of drinks i can make. I can make ice tea, hot tea, hot cocoa, cider, and yummy coffee. It\'s also very easy to use. The instructions were very easy to understand. This coffee maker does its job of serving me a good cup of joe. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8255, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'New Keurig I\'ve owned 2 keurigs in the past. The first one that came out then a small single serve one. This keurig is the most responsive one I have owned. It is touch screen I enjoy the setting to make ur coffee stronger and really enjoy the option that actually objectifies the volume (8 oz, 10 oz etc).  I haven\'t use the carafe option yet. I like the water filter on the back but not sure if it\'s necessary or not as I\'m on municipal water. I really like the white color as it looks elegant in my kitchen and matches with the cabinets and counters.'),
(8256, 13, 2, 4, '2016-01-02', 'Customer Service solved the problem on New Years Day! I\'m writing this for my mother who received the Keurig K200 for a Christmas gift. A friend had given her the KCup pods to use in the new Keurig, but to our dismay they were not usable. The OOPS message came up with 4 of the pods we tried..all different varities but usable in Keurigs. I decided to call the customer service # on the screen & they were quick to fix the problem. It seems that this Keurig pot is equipped with a laser to read the top of the pods & the pods we had were not newer pods. The new pods will have a lavender, grey or white ring on the edge of the pod top. Thank you very much to the customer service agent that assisted us last night.'),
(8257, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-28', 'Love it! I picked it up drain the Black Friday sale yesterday and am already in love. It was quick easy and a no-brainer to set up. It came with a few K cops but I\'ve already tried. I cannot wait to use less and save on money from coffee shops.'),
(8258, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-03', 'Stuff not included I would expect more to be included in the purchase.  There were no sample pods and I needed to buy the separate pod to make my own coffee.'),
(8259, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-05', 'Great customer service! It is not often that incredible, hassle-free customer service like what I experienced with Keurig is provided! My Keurig was 10 months old when it completely lost power. I read online that when this happens, it is pretty much irreversible so I made a call at 10:30 at night and was shipped a new machine two days later. They were beyond kind, and I am so thankful for the way I was treated by the company. I\'m sure they have the money to lose one customer, but I certainly felt like I was very important to them because of their intent to keep me happy! Thank you, Keurig!'),
(8260, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-23', 'A Great Brewer for those who enjoy a hot drink! I love this Brewer! It\'s sleek and sophisticated design goes well with other kitchen appliances.It also doesn\'t take up much space so those with a limited amount of counter space don\'t be worried. 40 ounces of water can be held in the reservoir at once and heats up in 3 minutes or less. For those on the go this is great for fast-paced mornings, it is also easy to use and it\'s touch screen gives you step by step directions. You can also control the strength of your coffee and I personally like my coffee weak so I\'m glad I am able to dictate that. Overall wonderful product, Keurig pulled through with this one, allowing me to skip the coffee shop before work!'),
(8261, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Awesome Looks great, easy to use and makes great coffee!'),
(8262, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-17', 'I will not purchase again I am disappointed with this coffee maker. I had a older keurig that was so much better. It died after a few years! This coffee maker plugs constantly after a few cups of coffee! It also will not accept some of the coffee pods that say they are keurig acceptable. So disappointed!'),
(8263, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-15', 'K250 Expierience I use my K250 Everyday! I love that its fast and that there are multiple cup sizes to choose from! The one and only down fall of my K250 experience is that it is noisy, but Ill take that as long as it continues giving me my coffee hot and fast!'),
(8264, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-31', 'This machine creates a cup of total and complete bliss. I genuinely love this product, not only is it way better than any other coffee maker or tea kettle, it\'s beautiful looking. It has a touch screen and step by step display. Also, you can program it to have a cup or carafe of your favorite coffee or tea waiting on you in the morning, afternoon, or evening. But you can also tell it it what kind of brew you want. It gives an option for a \"strong brew\", for those of you that like coffee that feels like a good morning slap in the face. What makes it special is, it\'s just so incredibly easy to you. It has a detachable water dispenser, so you doing have to play, try not to get a electrocuted. But it\'s good for any household, because each individual person, can have their favorite cup of coffee in under 3 minutes. It\'s good for someone on the go, or someone who likes to have their beverages at their leisure. But with an, \'on the go\' brewing speed. I\'ve always wanted one, I\'ve always wondered if it was all it was cracked up to be? It totally is. Why spend close to the same amount on something basic, when you can have something special. Keurig 2.0 is definitely special. And now that I use the K-Pods, I do see them in more and more grocery stores. So you don\'t HAVE to order everything online, but you can if you wanted to.'),
(8265, 13, 2, 4, '2016-09-16', 'K259 Works great We received this unit as a replacement for a Keurig K222 which was defect and under warranty. This unit is a bit smaller which we like and works perfectly so far. The water reservoir is not as accessible as at the old model, but that is no big inconvenience.'),
(8266, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-21', 'Lots to Love! There is so much to love about this little machine! I can\'t wait to see all the colors the brewer will come in! First, it\'s a nice, compact machine. We also have a K550 brewer, and it\'s about half the size. It\'s quiet and fast, and I LOVE the option for hot water (those with a previous 2.0 brewer will know what a big deal this is, you used to have to hold down the brew button and it might spit out a couple of ounces at a time!) Pros: -compact, quiet, easy to use, comes with a cleaning piece and descaling solution Cons: -no auto-off feature (and you have to hold down the power button for a bit for it to turn off, you can\'t just push and release) -reservoir is on the back of the machine, not the side, and a bit tricky to get it to seat properly until you get used to how it fits on there. If you\'re putting the machine under an upper cabinet in the kitchen, it\'ll be harder to fill the reservoir than other models Overall, I\'m really happy I received this machine in exchange for my review, and think it\'ll be perfect for small kitchens (or those that want to take up less space on their counters) and we\'re definitely taking it on vacation with us!'),
(8267, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-26', 'What\'s up with the \"opps\" message? Was so excited to get this new 2.0 Keurig. Got it in the turquoise color and it\'s so cute. HOWEVER, we soon noticed it only accepts \"K-brewed cups\" with a white rim. All our other older pods (that were recently purchased at a discount home store) like \"Tullys\", Grande Kaffe /Classic salted caramel, Celestial iced tea (sweet raspberry black tea & southern sweet black tea) do not work. Instead you get the error message....OOPS! Fortunately, our old Keurig will still brew the cups. Not a fan of this new machine, b/c of that issue.'),
(8268, 13, 2, 1, '2016-04-01', 'Disappointed I\'ve had 2 Mini kuerigs for some time but bought a 2.0 because it said it had 9 brew sizes. Not. Still can\'t get more than 10 ounces of coffee. Who has a mug that small?!?'),
(8269, 14, 2, 4, '2014-10-07', 'go ahead and buy it Great blender for the price. Blended and chopped ice very well. Just like any blender don\'t expect to fill this to the top. Used the right way it did it\'s job well.'),
(8270, 13, 2, 2, '2016-01-17', 'It\'s just OK This is my second Keurig 2.0. First one was a gift. It didn\'t read any of the pods so Keurig was very good about replacing it. The new one still has problems reading the pods. It reads some of the one in the box and not others. Frustrating. I don\'t like that it doesn\'t turn off. I unplug it, again very frustrating. I think whatever part is suppose to read the pods needs a lot of upgrading.'),
(8271, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'awesome coffee maker easier to use. sleek look. perfect for small counter.'),
(8272, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-28', 'I bought after my other unit crashed and burned. I was reluctant to spend this much money since I\'m the only one who drinks coffee in the home, but it was well worth this cost. The screen tells you what to do. The style is sleek, but a little larger than I expected. Don\'t let that scare you though because it still fit nice on my counter. I bough the Sandy Pearl color and it is GORGEOUS!!  I highly recommend this product.'),
(8273, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-11', 'Really recommend this system! We have loved having a Keurig in our house! My husband can quickly and easily brew his usual 10 oz. of dark roast coffee before heading off to work early in the morning, and I can brew a smaller amount later. No more big coffee pots half-full of unused coffee, and we can easily choose different flavors. This Keurig is extremely easy to use, and brewing time is very fast! I have also used the Keurig to brew cups of wellness teas, and hot cocoa. We honestly have no complaints about this product so far!'),
(8274, 14, 2, 1, '2015-02-18', 'This product doesn\'t work The blender doesn\'t blend simple ice cream, milk and strawberries. Motor bogs down and gets hot. I would not recommend this to anyone.'),
(8275, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-04', 'Coffee I love this Keurig coffee machine. It takes less room on my counter and I love the turquoise color. Other than for coffee, I also use this for hot water for tea and other needs.'),
(8276, 13, 2, 5, '2016-05-22', 'great product used daily for coffee or tea quick, easy to use, looks great in our remodeled kitchen no negatives that we have found'),
(8277, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Superb Product I bought this machine for a fantastic price and was therefore ready to make some compromises in terms of functionality and quality. However, I was beyond pleased to find it is an excellent machine.  The quality and ease of use are great. It brews a good cup of coffee in less than a minute. The only drawback is that travel mugs do not fit under the brewing port but it is simple to just transfer from a mug to a travel mug.'),
(8278, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Love it Love it! Had the mini, love this next step up.'),
(8279, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-21', 'Keurig is the best part of waking up! I am an everyday Keurig user and I wouldn\'t have it any other way! I love the flavor of the coffee that my Keurig gives me...when that stream of coffee begins the smell is AMAZING, makes me one happy mama! I love the option of the \"strong\" setting, although it seems to take a bit longer...the machine itself seems a bit slower than our old Keurig, but it\'s not as noisy and is definitely a bit more \"high tech\". Overall, I love it!'),
(8280, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-12', 'New To Keurig We finally made the move to a Keurig and so far it is EVERYTHING we expected. We have used them at friends and relatives houses and had to do it. NO more drip coffee makers!'),
(8281, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Super value I highly recommend.  Best value!'),
(8282, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'I would buy this product again if I had to. I use my Keurig every day and absolutely love it. I would recommend this product to anyone who is looking to buy a Keurig. The only negative is that I usually drink a 12-oz cup and this cup only goes to 10 oz. But, I just make 4 oz and using the same pod, make another 8 oz. Not a big deal. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(8283, 13, 2, 4, '2016-06-01', 'Great Service Touch panel failed after about 5 months of use. Keurig shipped me another under warrantee within 4 days. Great service, although it shouldn\'t have failed that soon!'),
(8284, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Keurig 2.0 Besides saving money on every cup of coffee, I absolutely love it.'),
(8285, 13, 2, 1, '2016-08-14', 'Not Nearly As Great As The Original Keurig Sadly my original Keurig died and I needed a replacement.  I though this smaller, sleeker model would fit the bill.  Sadly, it doesn\'t.  The water reservoir doesn\'t hold much and it has to be filled from the back of the machine.  So if you have your machine under a cabinet, it\'s quite inconvenient.  Also, I have NO idea how to change the filter.  I\'m prompted to do so but I can\'t find it and the manual doesn\'t tell me either.  If this were my only Keurig experience, I\'d never buy another one.  This thing stinks.  Spring for a pricier model.'),
(8286, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Nice brewer, a little disappointed I can\'t use old K-cups I bought this Keurig because my old one was, after several years of use, not brewing a full cup or sometimes wouldn\'t brew at all. This one was a decent price and had lots of fun color choices! I love how it brews and has an easy-to-use touch screen. The one problem I have with it (and I didn\'t understand or realize this when I bought it), is that you can\'t use certain K-cups in it. I have a BUNCH of coffee and tea products that I can\'t use in this because they don\'t have the check mark on them, but they are still a Keurig product! I wrote to them about it and their solution was \"give them to someone that can still use them in their brewer\". Well, for one thing, I paid good money for those and I don\'t feel like just giving away all my coffee and tea and I don\'t know anyone nearby that I can give them too. They did try and compensate by giving me two free boxes of coffee/tea with the purchase of two boxes. The trouble with that is they give you the same promotion code as when you bought the machine and you can\'t use it twice. Instead, of giving such bad advice and a code that you can\'t use, maybe they should give you a free reusable K-cup coffee filter that can work in the 2.0, because my old ones don\'t work in here either. While its a really nice brewer, I feel like I have to re-buy everything I already have! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8287, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-20', 'It\'s nice to have hot water so fast. Love the machine'),
(8288, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-31', 'Replace your old Keurig now because the 2.0 is great I used to keep a Keurig for my daily coffee and a drip coffee for when I had guests over. But after getting the new Keurig I\'ve said goodbye to drip coffee! This machine is great for my downtown apartment. I definitely needed the counter space the drip machine was taking up. It\'s a little on the pricey side but it\'s a great investment! I had my last Keurig for 4 years and only replaced it because I wanted to upgrade. 100% would purchase again!'),
(8289, 13, 2, 2, '2016-03-16', 'RECOGNIZE THE PODS!!! When it recognizes the pods, brews good tea/coffee... problem is IF. Does not recognize the carafe I bought even though it\'s made by Keurig and does not recognize most of the pods, even though they worked fine in my original Keurig brewer. So, unless you have tea bags for hot water which this dispenses well, save your money!'),
(8290, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-25', 'Love it!!! Have loved this Keurig brand so far. Easy to use and a large water capacity. Even at my 11-year-old son has no problem operating at. Also love the Sandy pearl color.'),
(8291, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-31', 'Great coffee maker! I got a great deal right before Christmas on this and it works great! Wish it had a timer and auto shut off but can\'t beat it for the price!'),
(8292, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Perfect Brewer , We love it. It was a present from my husband, we both have different taste and Keurig gives us many many options to choose from most quality brands, it is fast and very easy to use , We love it.'),
(8293, 13, 2, 3, '2015-07-02', 'doesn\'t fill mug more than halfway loved the look of this new brewer. but it doesn\'t fill my mug more than half way even on the 10 oz setting.'),
(8294, 13, 2, 1, '2016-10-25', 'Disappointed! Bought less than a year ago after first one stopped working after a year and now this one is acting up. Doesn\'t stop filling cup after 10 oz., pours very slowly even after cleaning several times, then shows it is reheating, but never reheats and just keeps showing the reheat icon. Buy a 3rd one in less than 2 years? Why should I??!!!'),
(8295, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-23', 'Wrong colors Need stainless steel color....none of these colors go with stainless steel appliances!!!! Great product, but does not match appliances! You need to make one in all silver!'),
(8296, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-06', 'Better than expected This keurig works better than expected. Coffee is brewed immediately with a very short wait, it\'s always hot and full of flavor. Worth the price. Thanks keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(8297, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-01', 'Good Keurig Model Bought this Keurig for Christmas for my husband Andrea he loves it! Easy use and clean up!'),
(8298, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-14', 'Brew a little drink a lot! This is my first Keurig and I couldn\'t be more excited to write about how amazing it is! It is SUPER easy to set up, quick to brew and quiet. The little touch screen gives clear step by step instructions on what to do next which is great. K-cups came with the Keurig which was amazing since I didn\'t have any just laying around but wanted to try it right away! My first cup was English Breakfast Tea. I\'m not a huge coffee drinker so tea is my preferable option and this tea was amazing. Fresh. It took me back to my first encounter with Breakfast Tea on my trip to Ireland a few years back. It is now my special treat on the mornings that the kids actually sleep in a little and I have some (rare) time for myself. I have even tried several of the coffee blends and they are very good! They are fresh and of higher quality. I prefer my coffee brewed over ice so I froze some of my favorite creamer and brewed it right over those cubes and it was amazing! It has me so excited for the warmer weather that is coming as it will replace my morning cup of hot tea. My husband has jumped right on the coffee train with me and drinks a LOT more of it than I do and is absolutely loving the Keurig .It\'s easy to make and maintain and no clean up after it\'s brewed right in to your cup! His one word after his first sip was, delicious. So all in all - 5 stars for the Keurig 2.0 machine itself as it is sleek, modern, and perfect for a home kitchen counter. I\'ve yet to read on other special things it can do but for the morning cup of coffee - it\'s perfect! I\'m excited to play with new settings and recipes and see just exactly all of the things that it will have to offer. I\'ve seen recipes for oatmeal, soups and more and I can\'t wait to try them out! The k-cups they sent with it are fantastic. There is quite the variety to choose from and each one I\'ve had so far is supper yummy! I\'m excited about expanding what I already know is going to be my k-cup collection and even learning about how to re-purpose the cups and grounds and make every little bit count! So if you\'re in the market for a new coffee maker - go for the higher end and snatch a Keurig - it\'s well worth every penny!'),
(8299, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-04', 'Our First Keurig First time users and we are converts. Like the idea that I can have tea and my husband coffee. Easy to accomodate company.. Also takes very little counter space.'),
(8300, 14, 2, 1, '2015-02-26', 'No Power I purchased this blender a few days ago. I went to use the blender last night and there was no power! I tried everything. I am waiting to hear back from Black & Decker concerning this.'),
(8301, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-26', 'Don\'t do it! Don\'t buy this item! I bought it, brought it home, plugged it in and it did not work. I got the \"oops\" message and never got past it. Had to spend 25 minutes on phone with Keurig customer service. The respresentative said the unit was most likely defective before I said anything. Wasted 4 K-cups trying to get it to work.'),
(8302, 13, 2, 3, '2015-07-26', 'Not impressed I drink a great deal of coffee. I like dark roast, extra bold. Bought this product while away from home for sometime. I have the old Keurig and to me it makes a much better cup of coffee than the one I just bought. I am disappointed because it was quite expensive.'),
(8303, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-24', 'Mini Starbucks I use my new Keurig between 5-6 times per week. Generally in the morning to kickstart my day from a long drive to work. The brewer has only one coord and \"installation\" is very simple. When you turn the brewer on, it begins a preheating stage which may bother a few as it takes anywhere from 30-60 seconds. Then you select the strength of your coffee and size and the brewing begins almost immediately. In comparison to previous versions, I believe this version is much easier to use, it feels faster, and is easy to clean and maintain. Noise levels are tolerable and the touch display is convenient. The new water tank is convenient for such a small sized Keurig in that I don\'t have to add 8 ounces of water to my Keurig each time I want a cup of coffee. With that being said, I feel that the primary flaw, as with all Keurigs is that whenever the water falls down to a certain level in the tank, you can no longer have a cup of coffee, tea, etc. You must have it filled to a certain unmarked point in the water tank to have coffee. Not a big deal but I wish the water could all be used before having to add more water. I would highly recommend this product to anyone who drinks a cup of coffee once a day or more, especially at the office. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8304, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-11', 'Keurig is awesome! We bought the orange Keurig for our office, and we all absolutely love it! The look fits right in with the rest of the decor, and the functionalities of the Keurig make everyone love it! Switching the cup size from 4oz, to 10oz is super amazing that we control how much of our beverage we want. In addition, if you leave the pod out, it has an option to pour hot water for all the tea lovers out there! I know we have a few in our office and they enjoy that aspect of our Keurig.  This is a great purchase, I even bought one for my own home!!'),
(8305, 13, 2, 1, '2016-04-06', 'Would never by the 2.0 again ever This is the worst brewer I have bought. This is my 4th Keurig I have purchased and this is by far the one I hate. I have had it replaced once already. I buy most of my coffee on the Keurig site and only a few actually work in the brewer. I am one to try new coffee and now I can\'t for fear it will not brew in this brewer. Can\'t wait until it breaks so I can get a different one.'),
(8306, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-24', 'Disappointed product and selfish idea I got the 2.0 last week as a gift, and I brought 50 variety cups. I tried 10 cups and only 2 worked. I searched online and I found that many consumers have already complained about how selfish the 2.0 is. It only reads specific cup which has special print on the cover of the cup, so the machine itself even cannot process some of the old K-cup. What a selfish idea!'),
(8307, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-10', 'Love this machine! I have been using a Keurig for the last five years.  I decided to upgrade as my old one wouldn\'t stay on and took a long time to heat up.  I was a little leary after reading some of the reviews.  However,  I absolutely love this one!  I love the different size options and the hot water option.  I did get the error message about the wrong type of K-cup, but I just opened the top and lowered it again and it worked.  It\'s so quick and easy.  My only complaint would be that the water container is in an awkward place and doesn\'t seems to need to be filled fairly often.  Other than that, I love it and would recommend it to anyone.'),
(8308, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-11', 'Keurig addict I bought this smart keurig for my RV travels.  This is the 5 th keurig that I own.  I know you can only use one at a time!  What can I say, I\'m an addict! I love the smaller counter print (I guess that\'s what you call it,it takes up less counter space). Don\'t  have a lot of that it the RV. Same great quality. Same great coffee. Nothing beats that exquisite fresh coffee with each cup.  Oh the color is a true bonus! My entire kitchen is turquoise !'),
(8309, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'We love it! Nice design, easy to use, and fast.  The digital screen tells you what to do next, and is very polite!'),
(8310, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-27', 'Love these Bewers I love keurig brewes, this is my third one, the first two were the orginal brewers, first one broke in a move cross country, I have had them for 4+ years and recieved the orange as a gift for christmas, It is usally just me that drinks coffee with my spouse ocassinaly, but I love the fact that when I do have people over I can brew a kraft, the customer service has always been great, and this is nice because if also gives you the option to use a water filter as well.'),
(8311, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-04', 'Wake up Makes a delious cup of coffee. No fuss no mess. Very simple way for a cup of coffee when you are waking up in the morning, afternoon or evening. Only wish is that it wasn\'t more heavy duty. Why everything is made from plastic.'),
(8312, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Telecommuter\'s Dream! I telecommute, so I often miss out on having a ready supply of coffee at hand like in-office worker have. But now, with my Keurig 2.0, I have amazing coffee at my fingertips. I can make one cup at a time, so I don\'t waste any of my precious Java. The unit stores easily on my kitchen counter right underneath the cabinets. I use it multiple times a day and it consistently delivers a quality cup of coffee. Game, set and match to the Keurig!!! \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(8313, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-22', 'Perfect! Love this coffee maker! It\'s the perfect size and I got it in Sandy Pearl which is beautiful!'),
(8314, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-17', 'Have a GREAT Morning with Keurig 2.0 I instantly fell in love with the k250! Great product! Easy, sleek, sexy design of the k250 allows this coffee maker to fit in just about anywhere. After brewing my first cuppa joe I was hooked! The menu screen is EASY and intuitive. The Strong Coffee and Hot Chocolate options in the menu are great additions and brew exactly what they say they will. I\'m impressed with the k250! I\'ll be investing in a carafe today!'),
(8315, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-24', 'Right Bells and Whistles I had a complex Keurig and it eventually succumbed.  I talked to friends who have this machine and bought one myself.  Prices have come down greatly over the years.  This has only the \"bells and whistles\" I would use with cup sizes and cleaning notices.  This is perfect for home!'),
(8316, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-27', 'In love with 2.0! Before purchasing this new Keurig, I had a MiniPlus for 5 years. As much as I loved my mini, I love 2.0 even more! I love the 40 oz reservoir, the multitude of cup sizes, the new K-Mug sizes, the fact that I can fit my travel mugs underneath and the very happy shade of teal. It also doesn\'t take up much more space than my mini. I use my Keurig at least once per day and love that, because of the reservoir, I can leave it on and hot, just in case I choose to have a second cup. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. And thank you for 2.0!'),
(8317, 13, 2, 1, '2016-11-12', '2nd try, 2nd failure Our first brewer couldn\'t seem to heat enough and was replaced promptly by Keurig.   Even though I clean this 2nd brewer (same model) several times per month, it seems to become blocked (under pressure) rather often; although I follow the instructions it may or may not (the current condition) unblock to make coffee.  Would we be better off with one of the higher-priced brewers?  We used to love the coffee even though we had to heat it in the microwave to get it hot enough.  All suggestions to get this thing fixed would be appreciated.'),
(8318, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Best Idea from Keurig The 250 has solved the issues I had with the inconvenience of the mini and the size of the larger systems. Keurig has developed the perfect solution for limited space and convenience with the 250 system'),
(8319, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-24', 'A great little machine for a great price! So let me just start off by saying how beautiful the sandy pearl color is! I love that they offer so many colors, but this color gives the keurig a luxurious feeling without the expense. This is my first Keurig and I am more than excited to use it after using my parents k400 series model (I was in love). The K200 offers the best of both worlds; its compact and takes up less counter space ,yet it still offers the same great variety of drinks and of course the ease of use. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review\"\"'),
(8320, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Keurig is Great I luv this coffee maker...easy to use and ordering from target was easy and delivery was quick'),
(8321, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-14', 'Stopped Working We bought this Keurig for a Special Education class to use in their coffee cart business at the middle school. We bought the Keurig in September and now it no longer works. It will slowly drip out the coffee and then it will stop. I have one of the older models and have had it for years, with no problems.'),
(8322, 13, 2, 4, '2015-12-25', 'Almost Perfect I love the size of this brewer (it is my 4th Keurig for various reasons) and the fact that the reservoir is in the back rather than on the side. However, I was very disappointed that it does NOT have auto shut off. I am also disappointed that some Keurig pods I have will not work in it...especially my peach tea.'),
(8323, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-27', 'I love mine Keurig 2.0 I absolutely love my Keurig, I will never use anything else! Its so easy to use. Works perfectly and is very quiet compared to the other version Keurig I had. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8324, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-27', 'LOVE IT!!!!! This is my second Keurig. I tried to go back to a regular coffee brewer after my first Keurig needed to be replaced after 5 years of constant use..... and I lasted a few months. I really missed having a Keurig! I purchased the Keurig K200 in Sandy Pearl yesterday and absolutely love it. It is smaller and less bulky than my 2010 machine. Set up was a snap! Love the touch screen and water reservoir. If you use filtered water from your refrigerator, the reservoir fits easily in the water niche and doesn\'t take long to fill. Overall I am thrilled with this machine. Welcome back, Keurig!!!'),
(8325, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-26', 'K475 We received our Brewer yesterday (03/25/2016) and decided to use the same day, we were very curious to see how it would work. My daughters were equally excited so we decided to make hot chocolate. My husband washed before and ran the hot water before the first brew. Everything was really easy, then just put the little cup in and then delicious hot chocolate comes out! That easy! I still want to try other flavored/ different beverages, but for now it seems like it works great and we definetely love it!'),
(8326, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Love my Keurig! I love how fast my keurig works and that it works with not only coffee but tea and iced drinks as well! So glad I got this product, it makes it easy to grab something on the go or just when I feel like it. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8327, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'I love my 2.0! I use my 2.0 everyday I make single cups and carafe\'s. I love it, it\'s SO quiet compared to my previous Keurig. The only complaint I have is the instruction manual doesn\'t really tell how to use the carafe very well, or how to set up the filter (if you\'ve never used one before that is helpful to know). It came with a descaler and that was a great surprise, you have to buy the carafe separate. Thanks, Keurig, for the free Pods for this review!!'),
(8328, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-21', 'Slim and simple I love the design because the water tank is so much easier to deal with now and it looks so much slimmer. The touch screen with different cup sizes is so easy to use and convenient.'),
(8329, 13, 2, 3, '2015-08-11', 'Keurig 2.0 K250 I like that this product allows me to drink my coffee without having to brew a whole pot. I love the Turquoise color. I don\'t like that you can only use Keurig cups in the machine without trying to override inherent protocols. I had a Keurig K10 MINI Plus Brewing System before this one, and could brew my own coffee in a reusable cup. I can\'t tell the difference in the taste of the coffee using the Strong option. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8330, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-04', 'Just a cup I use the product everyday for my morning on to work cup of coffee. The biggest size it makes is 10 ounces, I would love if it made up to 12 ounces. You can make a carafe with 4 cups, but you have to purchase the carafe separately and you have to be special k-cups that are made for the carafe. I also feel super wasteful using the k-cups and just tossing them after each use. It is easy to use and has an option to do just hot water which is nice for many purposes. It has a built in water filter and comes with cleaning supplies. I have not tried to clean it yet so I cannot speak to that. It doesn\'t take up much counter space and has a sleek design. Comparing it to a hamilton beach that is similar but is a bit bigger as the 4-cup maker is actually 8 cups and sits on the side. It would be useful and more worth the price if the Keurig came with the carafe for brewing more.'),
(8331, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-31', 'Great color and works well The water reservoir has to be refilled often. Other than that it is easy to use and heats quickly. I wish there was a setting to start it automatically in the morning.'),
(8332, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Great Christmas Buy Been looking all over for a white Keurig .  this color is very hard to find, especially on sale.  Target not only had them they were the lowest price I have found this season.  Love these coffeemakers and am especially glad to have this one.  It takes up very little counter space.  Never wastes coffee.  Your coffee is always fresh and hot.  Since buying this brand a few years ago I find that I try many more brands of coffee than when I was limited to a pot or carafe only.'),
(8333, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-26', 'bronx willie got it for my wife on Christmas. she loves it. to me the price was great and it keeps me from walking 5 blocks to dunkin donuts everyday. The shipping was right on time. and it was easy to order. so this made everything great to me. I will be using Target.com again in the future.'),
(8334, 13, 2, 5, '2016-11-01', 'Oh! I Love This Kuerig 2.0 With a slimmer line and digital display, this 2.0 Kuerig beats my older one hands down. I have a small kitchen and counter space is premium real estate for appliances. This new design takes up very little space. And, oh! Those colors! 10 to choose from! I bought the one in Oasis - just the prettiest pale teal beach color you can imagine! I like the filter system and that it is practically plug and go. It brews the perfect cup or caraf of coffee or tea - depending on the k cup you prefer. This little beauty is saving me trips to Starbucks.'),
(8335, 13, 2, 5, '2016-05-17', 'Looks Purchased this to replace an older model that was acting up. Got a white one to match my other appliances. Love it! It works great and love its versatility!'),
(8336, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-15', 'New Keurig user and couldn\'t be happier! I just bought my first Keurig and couldn\'t be happier with my purchase. I am a little upset that some of the pods that my mom gave me to try won\'t work with the 2.0 but other than that I love it!'),
(8337, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-18', 'Quick, Easy, and Awesome Since getting our Keurig we have started drinking more cold coffee\'s, and teas, and quit going to the coffee shop. We love the variety of K cups Keurig offers. However we have found some in other brands we would love to try as well, but this Keurig only take Keurig bran K Cups. While we understand the reasoning behind it, we wish we were able to purchase and use whichever brand we would like.The other con would be that we wish it came with the carafe rather than us having to purchase one at an extra $30. Pro\'s .. we love how fast it is, that we can brew hot and cold, and that if we just want hot water for a regular tea bag, that is possible as well. We love the fact that we can enjoy coffee shop type drink at a fraction of the price and do not have to drive the fifteen miles to get them. My husband is THRILLED with our Keurig and I am as well. Easy to use, great selection, and quick. If we were able to use any brand K cups and it came with the carafe I would have given it the full five stars.'),
(8338, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-20', 'I AM SO HAPPY WITH MY NEW KEURIG 2.0 K250 I HAD A PROBLEM WITH A GIFT KEURING AND YOUR SERVICE STAFF SENT A NEW ONE. NOTHING BUT GOOD THINGS TO SAY ABOUT MY NEW ONE. WORKED LIKE A CHARM FROM TYHE MINUTE IT ARRIVED AND GOT SET UP. ;THANKS KEURIG JEANNINE'),
(8339, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-10', 'Great product 3 weeks later I bought this K200 brewer about 3 weeks ago and am in love with it. It brews fast, great cups of coffee at the literal press of a button. I use it every morning, multiple times a day, as I frequently drink coffee. Brewing a cup is easy as fill with water, insert pod, and brew. The downside is the max cup size for the pods is 10oz which is a bit less than the size of my cups. Also, it is very difficult to ensure you are buying the proper 2.0 pods in the store. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8340, 14, 2, 4, '2015-01-27', 'Recommend! I have always had bad luck with blenders, but this one is fantastic! I only use it for smoothies, but it blends with ease! Great price, great product, easy to clean.'),
(8341, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-26', 'Love this product! I drink coffee everyday, and find the Keurig to be extremely convenient. I don\'t have to spend money everyday at Starbucks and the process of making a cup is easy and quick. The different flavors of K-cups is great if I\'m ever craving something different. The machine is a little noisy, but at the end of the day, it gets the job done efficiently and you won\'t be stuck waiting in any lines.'),
(8342, 13, 2, 4, '2016-11-07', 'Coffee pot The color is so vibrant. Really stands out in my kitchen.'),
(8343, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Great Coffee, Greater Coffee Maker I LOVE my Keurig 2.0 k250!!! I use this product everyday and it\'s perfect for when my roommates and I are in a rush to get to our classes. It was easy to pack up and move from my dorm to my apartment, and it\'s so easy to use. Best of all- IT STAYS CLEAN!'),
(8344, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-10', 'Great upgrade! I am a huge coffee drinker, I\'ve had Keurigs for years. This is my fav because it is so more efficient in space and has so many more bells and whistles!!'),
(8345, 13, 2, 3, '2016-05-25', 'Comparison to my old Elite Yes, the 2.0 does clog easier than my previous Elite but the plastic gizmo does the trick in a snap so no problem. Can\'t believe in this day and age that it does not shut off automatically. Feature that I miss the most.'),
(8346, 13, 2, 2, '2016-03-12', 'Looks aren\'t everything While it looks good; I like my beverages HOT and this falls short, short, short! Disappointed that it stops at 10oz for the standard K-cup. The amount of grounds in the cup can surely support a 14 oz volume of water (no need for \"future\" Keurig brand pods); I have to run it a second time for the extra 4 oz.'),
(8347, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Awesome coffee brewer for home and office We drink a lot of coffee in our office. We used to use traditional coffee machine and always had leftover coffee in the pot which went to waste because they taste bad afterawhile. So we decided to purchase Keurig. Keurig 2.0 system is perfect because everyone gets to drink fresh tasting coffee that brews instantly whenever they crave for one. In the morning we brew K carafe which serves about 4 people using one carafe pod. Others choose whatever they want to drink and everyone is happy. There are huge selection of coffees and other drinks. This is good because there are some people that prefers hot cocoa or teas instead of coffee. Keurig 2.0 covers everybody.'),
(8348, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-04', 'Gret machine works great. smaller design than the vue but still holds plenty of water and i dont have to search high and low for pods thats actually work. I love it'),
(8349, 13, 2, 5, '2016-08-13', 'DONT BUY A KERIG MACHINE! I used to like coffee but I decided to get a kerig machine because my husband doesn\'t drink coffee and I thought a regular coffee maker just seemed to waste the coffee (can\'t just make 1 cup). But now I am TOTALLY ADDICTED TO COFFEE! my family tried an intervention and send me to rehab but it was no use. There are so many delicious flavors to try and in my opinion it\'s better than coffee house coffee. If you switch to this coffee maker, just be aware you will not be able to drink coffee out of a regular machine ever again. This particular machine is great coz it has never jammed which a plus when u are shaking bad for a fix at 5:30am.'),
(8350, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-03', 'Some good upgrades, some not so great I upgraded from a mini-keurig that I had for 2 years. I like that this has the water reservior so I don\'t have to add water every time, but it takes a long time to pre-heat the water. The machine does not turn off automatically, and I have to adjust the cup size every single time even though I make a 10 ounce cup every time.'),
(8351, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-15', 'Best Early Christmas Present! Bought this as an early Christmas present and it was by far the best decision! Cannot attest to it\'s longevity, but it did replace our old workhorse of a Keurig that lasted for 5 years (with only 2 descaling cycles...although I wouldn\'t recommend). The sizing options and brew strength options are fantastic, and the coffee tastes amazing every time!'),
(8352, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'I would recommend the new keurig highly The new color and sleek design make it ideal in small spaces'),
(8353, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-28', 'Great office coffee maker I bought this machine for my office staff use. It has been a big hit, its easy to use and the beverages are ready quickly. When using a conventional coffee maker the brew would sometimes sit for a long time on the warmer and end up burnt and bitter. Now every cup is fresh and delish with no waste. Thanks for the free pods Keurig!'),
(8354, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-26', 'great tasting coffee!! easy set up, quick brew'),
(8355, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Best Little Brewer! We have this model in our office, and one at home. It works great, is fast, convenient, and versatile! Love it.'),
(8356, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Obsessed! For the amount of coffee my household consumes, I can\'t believe we didn\'t upgrade sooner. We are a Keurig house, and had a K45 for the past few years. It was awesome...then we got this guy, and boy are we in love. It looks so sleek on our counter, and technology challenged husband even can use the touchscreen with ease! The carafe is amazing and It makes life so much more convienent when we want to drink more than one cup at a time. I think if it wasn\'t apparent before, this coffee maker seals the deal for us being loyal to Keurig!'),
(8357, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Love my new Keurig 2.0 k200 I have been waiting to get my first Keurig and when I saw the Off-White 2.0 k200 I bought it immediately. It works perfectly, easy, quick and very user friendly. I love the color - Off-White plus it comes in ALOT of other colors, even Purple!'),
(8358, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-05', 'Great Gift Great gift for my son-in-law. Easy to use and praytical'),
(8359, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-04', 'Skeptical I was skeptical because of the negative reviews I kept seeing; plastic taste in the coffee, complicated. So far I have experienced NONE of these issues. It\'s amazing how much less coffee you waste with these machines. You make what you want and that\'s it! i\'m OBSESSED!'),
(8360, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-04', 'Plastic Taste I spent 2 hours on the phone with customer service. They were so patient and di everything to help. We did multiple vinegar rinses plus up to 12 water rinses and still the taste and smell of plastic was evident. We exchanged the brewer and went through he same process. I was determined to fix it. Unfortunately after a couple of cups of coffee, the taste came back. Had my previous Keurig for 4 years....'),
(8361, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-08', 'Great for a little coffee Don\'t expect to put a Starbucks tumbler under this - it won\'t fit. The most you can get at one time is 10 oz. so I had to get creative and do two 6 oz. rounds to fill my mug (I like coffee!) so if 10 oz. is enough coffee for you, this is perfect. It works beautifully - I just have to buy the Keurig tumbler to fit this model.'),
(8362, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Glad I finally Switched Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review! I wish I had bought a Keurig years ago. Really love the consistently good flavor of my bold, strong coffees.'),
(8363, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-28', 'Do not buy this machine New Keurig, started clogging every third cup. Apparently will not use all Keurig-type cups. Frustrating waste of money. Do not buy this machine.'),
(8364, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Best coffee maker ever I wanted this coffee maker for so long but it\'s a bit expensive. Overall, it is the best. Easy to use. My daughter can make her hot chocolates and understands it. It\'s a good value'),
(8365, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-02', 'Great system for office Purchased one at a great price with free k-cups and carafes at a local electronics/appliance store. Small, compact, stylish product that sits in my office. Convenience is a great feature. DRM may be an issue for some, but not a problem for me as I buy K-cups anyway. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8366, 13, 2, 1, '2015-08-10', 'Sadly my first and last Keurig This was my first Keurig I was tracking the package I was so excited. I wanted this for work and I was going to buy one for my home. It felt like Christmas when the package arrived at my home. I put everything together my sister was so jealous when she was saw what came in. I went by all the directions setting everything up. I hit continue and the message Please add water appeared on the display. I thought it was my mistake. I emptied the water put more back in I made sure everything was put in right. Still \'add water please\' would not go away. I looked it up it had something to do with the sensory couldn\'t read that the water was in there. Something about that you need impurities in the water I don\'t know. Apparently the county water is cleaner than I thought. So it was returned the next day sadly. I don\'t feel like going through this again so my plan B is Mr. Coffee I heard those were okay too.'),
(8367, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Compact size same GREAT tasting Cofee Use this brewer every day!! Home, Office or Ship, it works GREAT! Thanks Keurig-, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8368, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-06', 'First Time Keurig Owner I\'ve been using a multi-cup coffeemaker for years, and could never bring myself to splurge on a Keurig since I\'m the only one who drinks coffee in our house. After trying the Keurig K250*, I\'d be lying if I said that I could ever see myself going back to my old coffeemaker! PROS: This has been so easy to use. The machine heats up quickly and makes a nice HOT cup of coffee. My old maker didn\'t even spit out coffee this hot, so it\'s nice to get coffee at the temperature it should be. Since I started using the Keurig, I\'ve also learned that I\'ve never made a proper cup of coffee. I would sleepily stumble to my coffeemaker, dump a little coffee in the filter and turn it on. Then, I\'d dump half a cup of creamer into it just to cover up the flavor, which was different every time. I love that the Keurig takes the guess out of measuring. I get a great tasting cup of coffee every time. I\'ve even discovered that I LOVE my coffee without creamer. French Roasts and Hazelnuts not only smell great, but they taste divine now too! I can get a few days of use out of the machine before it reminds me that I need to add more water. It\'s a little annoying, but with my old maker, I had to fill it every day, so that\'s just me being lazy. haha CONS: No, major cons. I didn\'t really find too much that I didn\'t like about the machine. It is a little noisy. Nothing super loud, but louder than my old maker and I do worry that it will wake up the kiddo if I\'m trying to brew a cup during naptime since their bedroom is right off the kitchen. It was a lot bigger than my old machine and does take up a good amount of space in our tiny apartment kitchen. It\'s not the largest machine in the world, but I\'m not sure if I would recommend it for apartment/dorm living or for anyone who had little counter space. I wish it had a clock/timer function like my old maker, but that\'s nothing that would keep me from purchasing this machine. It is true that this machine can ONLY use the 2.0 K-cups with the special white ring on them. There are plenty of ways around this, but the simplest solution is just to buy a 2.0 reusable k-cup. They\'re easily accessible for purchase in most stores. I picked one up and have been using it for weeks, without issue, in my K250 2.0 brewer. Overall, I\'m very glad that I got the chance to try this machine out for myself. The pros definitely outweigh the cons, and I would recommend this machine. [*I received this product complimentary for testing purposes from Influenster. All thoughts expressed are my own.]'),
(8369, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Love the new colors I purchased a mint color Keurig already have one in white but couldn\'t resist getting another one I love the functionality of the coffee machine it absolutely makes my morning go by easy and efficiently and great for when I have company'),
(8370, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Color Oasis make my Keurig even more beautiful I bought 2 in Oasis color for Christmas gift so no idea how the machine operate, or how easy of use.  Great size for counter tops, versatility, and convenience.  Love that it can dispense hot water for instant noodles cup. Hopefully this built to last for awhile.'),
(8371, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-25', 'not working with keurig brand kcups I received this as a Christmas present. It said that it only worked with Keurig branded kcups, to which I have MANY. I tried SEVERAL of them (different varieties) and EVERY SINGLE once of them provided the \"oops\" message saying they did not work. VERY DISAPPOINTING!'),
(8372, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-18', 'Better than my older model Easy to set up, and clean. Easy to use menu, and coffee come out nice and hot. I haven\'t seemed to figure out how to power down the unit without having to completely unplug it though.'),
(8373, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-10', 'LOVE MY KEURIG!!!! I love this Brewer! It\'s sleek and sophisticated design goes well with other kitchen appliances.It also doesn\'t take up much space so those with a limited amount of counter space don\'t be worried. 40 ounces of water can be held in the reservoir at once and heats up in 3 minutes or less. For those on the go this is great for fast-paced mornings, it is also easy to use and it\'s touch screen gives you step by step directions. You can also control the strength of your coffee and I personally like my coffee weak so I\'m glad I am able to dictate that. Overall wonderful product, Keurig pulled through with this one, allowing me to skip the coffee shop before work!'),
(8374, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Perfect for the Office I wanted a Keurig brewer for use at the office and this one is perfect. It is compact in size yet versatile in terms of coffee strength and cup size. It\'s easy to use, and most importantly, it makes a great cup of coffee. I considered the smaller K10 or K130 models, but had concerns about their durability after reading a number of reviews on those models. The K250 seems to be well-made, so I don\'t expect any such problems with it. I understand that the K250 will not accept certain incompatible K-cups, but this is really not that much of an issue to me as there are plenty of choices available in Keurig K-cups. Overall, I\'m very pleased with this product and would recommend it to others. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8375, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-15', 'WORST brewer I have ever had! This is absolutely the worst brewer Keurig makes. You may get a _ of a cup of coffee or it almost overflows. And if you want to make more than one cup of coffee, you will have to unplug the brewer and start over. I DO NOT RECOMMEND ANYONE BUYING THIS MODEL. It is a waste of money!'),
(8376, 13, 2, 2, '2015-08-04', 'Keurig 2.0 Not Suitable for making larger cups Have previously owned older models of Keurig brewers. In order to make a larger cup, we use the same K-cup twice. However, when you try to use the K-cup twice with the 2.0 system, it tears the top and bottom of the K-cup and most of the coffee grounds end up in the cup. Took 2.0 back and purchased a K40 which is better suited for our requirements. 2.0 works very well for smaller cup sizes but not suitable for our needs. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8377, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-17', 'Perfect cup everytime! I don\'t drink a lot of coffee and so this brewer is perfect for me. I can make a cup fast and easy anytime I want. I love that it is touch screen and the generalized pictures of the cup sizes are a great help to those, like me, who have no idea how many ounces are in my favorite cup. Its 10 by the way. The design is great and it fits perfectly in my tiny kitchen. The only thing I would change is to add a timer. I would love to wake up to cup brewing! Other than that it is amazing!'),
(8378, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-14', 'Great New Product! I was so excited to get to try the new Keurig 2.0 K200 Brewing System. It is very quiet, and fast. It also looks very stylish in my kitchen. I love that it comes with a built in filter, so I can use tap water with it. The only thing I do not like is that you can only use the new k-cups. I recently bought a bunch of decaf k-cups and I now cannot use them.'),
(8379, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Everything you could possibly ask for The Keurig K200 is a great little machine! Stylish, compact, and a great value. The touch screen is responsive and easy to understand. Really couldn\'t be simpler. Makes a great cup of coffee too! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8380, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-18', 'I Love my Keurig 2.0! I\'ve been drinking coffee for about 6 years and every time I\'ve tried to make it at home never came out right, so I\'m a DD perks and Starbucks Gold member..but now l\'m able to make a perfect cup every time at home.'),
(8381, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'The best product to start your morning Before buying a keurig, I would use a french press to make my coffee in the morning. That became very tedious and time consuming every day. I thought that a keurig machine would be lacking in flavor, but I was wrong after testing it out. The coffee is just as rich and smooth as before, except now I have many more varieties to try out. The most outstanding difference is the time it takes to make the coffee and lack of cleanup required. My only concern is the size selection for just water. It only offers 4oz and 6oz for water, which really is not enough for a hot cup of water (at least 8-10oz). Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8382, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-07', 'Love it ! nice bold red goes perfect in my kitchen without taking up a lot of counter space!'),
(8383, 14, 2, 5, '2015-12-08', 'Easy purchase Bought online and picked up in store in just mins. Was easy and quick. Love the new blender'),
(8384, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-27', 'A gift Very happy!  The color is beautiful and the ease with which to use and clean are fabulous.'),
(8385, 13, 2, 2, '2016-04-23', 'I do not like this product you have to clean it every 4 uses so we drink a ton of coffee. the pot needs cleaned after every 4 uses. I like the one my daughter has its one of the first ones made. This is such a pain'),
(8386, 14, 2, 4, '2014-12-15', 'Replacement blender I broke my blender and this is a good replacement.'),
(8387, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-19', 'Fun Machine!! Bought it about 3 weeks ago and love it! I\'ve wanted one for awhile but waited because I didn\'t know if my husband would object. He started making drinks immediately and does so every day.'),
(8388, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-22', 'Love my new brewer I love that my new brewer matches the dcor in my kitchen. I haven\'t had any problems that I have read in other reviews about this brewer. I have owned 2 other Keurigs and the customer service that has been provided is phenomenal.'),
(8389, 13, 2, 2, '2015-09-29', 'Very Disappointed I was very disappointed when I received my new Keurig only to find out it does not brew a 12oz cup of coffee with a regular K-cup. I purposely purchased it because of the color, brewer size and various cup size brewing. It was advertised that it had nine brew sizes which is incorrect unless you use various sized kcups. Very disappointed as I wish I still had my old Keurig.'),
(8390, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-11', 'We are enjoying this on weekends We enjoy this for the weekends. I like the flavors while my husband sticks to the basic roast. During the week we still use our regular pot as we need enough to fill our travel mugs on the way out the door.'),
(8391, 13, 2, 1, '2016-07-25', 'Exploding pods Given as present last Christmas. Trouble brewing more than one or two cups in a row without having to do complete cleaning. Even this doesn\'t prevent the explosion on the next cup. Talked to a service rep that sent out new interior parts. Helped briefly but now it\'s a guess as to whether you get a cup of coffee or cup of grinds and big mess on counter. Have been ordering and using pods from you. Disappointed at best'),
(8392, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-14', 'Not a fan... We have owned a Keurig for several years and ours was starting to malfunction at times so we bought a new one. What a disappointment. It doesn\'t brew as much as our old one, a pod (that it will actually accept) basically melted in the machine and then we had an abundance of coffee grounds in our cups. Was returned within 48 hours and will continue to use our old one.'),
(8393, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', 'LOVE IT I use the product every day and I absolutely love it. It was kind of difficult at first to figure out how to set it up, but once that is done, it is very easy to use.'),
(8394, 13, 2, 4, '2016-11-23', 'Great coffee maker Super user friendly and took no time to set up. I paid for basic shopping at got it in 4 days! I love this and the color is so pretty!'),
(8395, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-04', 'Very Disappointed Coffee tastes good, but it not brew a hot cup. It\'s warm - instead of hot. Very disappointed. I would like this to give this a good review - but I can\'t.'),
(8396, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', '2nd Keurig purchased after the 1st original broke 2016 I am happy with my 2.0 Keurig I love how it has filter I love how it dispenses hot water for tea or apple cider I also happy with the different sizes of pods it can use'),
(8397, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-09', 'Great system! Beautiful new colors! I purchased this model because my husband has wanted one with the reservoir. This one is perfect. Love the option of individual cup or carafe. I would like to have a refillable pod in order to brew a 10 or 12 ounce cup as we prefer a larger cup.'),
(8398, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-05', 'Love My Keurig I love this coffee maker. It\'s very easy to operate and since I am the only who drinks coffee in the house it\'s great to be able to make one cup at a time.'),
(8399, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Great Product for its Compact Size I bought this Keurig 2.0 to replace our old Mr.Coffee Keurig Brewer. Completely happy with the purchase, it gets hotter compared to the old one and is really easy to use. The size of the brewer is perfect since we use it on the boat where we live all summer. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8400, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-12', 'Plastic Taste Received this product as a gift. After years of using my old Keurig Mini , I was excited to get the new 2.0. Bottom line, I went back to using my old keurig mini after about 2 weeks. Nothing I do removes the burnt plastic taste from my coffee. I have soaked all removable parts (water reservoir, k-cup holder, etc) in white vineagar over night, spent an hour running white vinegar and water cleanses through the machine, and I even washed all the removable parts in the dishwasher (something you\'re not supposed to do but it was my last resort). Nothing I do removes the plastic taste and smell. Everything I try to brew is undrinkable. Reading the reviews from other 2.0 owners, I see I am not the only one drinking coffee that tastes like a burnt barbie doll. I have been a loyal customer for years, and even recruited my parents to the brand (my mom owns a coffee shop so this was quiet a feat), but I am now fearful of the plastic being used in the new 2.0 brewers. This will probably be the last Keurig product I use.'),
(8401, 13, 2, 1, '2016-10-12', 'Darn it Only used my new Kuerig a few times and it stopped brewing.  Again'),
(8402, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-31', 'Keurig Purchased as a gift, no complaints from the recipients.'),
(8403, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-09', 'Size Much bigger unit than expected.  Wish it was more the size of one cup unit'),
(8404, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-20', 'GREAT BREWING SYSTEM Love this Keurig! Having a setting to make stronger coffee is definitely a plus, as is having a setting for only hot water! Perfect size for my kitchen.'),
(8405, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-08', 'Wonderful product I use this every morning. It is so simple to use and brews quickly. It even heats up more quickly than it said it would. When I first got it, which was last week, it wouldn\'t brew a 10oz cup whn using a k-cup. Only 8oz would come out. However, I could get 10oz of hot water. I called and they quickly replaced the part that held the k-cups. It now brews 10oz with a k-cup, so I am very pleased. I couldn\'t ask anything more than this. I like having a bunch of choices since drinking the same thing over and over gets boring to me. Thanks Keuring!'),
(8406, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-09', 'great product! Love our first Keurig! We are tea drinkers and wanted a way to have hot water for us and choice of coffee, etc. for our friends.  It really saves by not having to throw out a pot full of coffee when we don\'t have the right kind (decaf, dark roast, etc.)'),
(8407, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Keurig Love this product best decision for coffee I\'ve made!'),
(8408, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Great for work I have a K350 at home and love it. I got tired of the nasty coffee at work and bought this unit to use at work. Now I can drink coffee at work again. Happiness'),
(8409, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-18', 'Wonderful Great brewer. Maybe a little slow compared to its bigger brothers but still good. Like it more than the older non 2.0 unit I had before. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8410, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-31', 'Best coffee maker Bought two aa a gift.  Very happy family members. Love the color. Excited to use the carafe and reusuable filter. Great gift ideas.'),
(8411, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-03', 'Coffee maker Love the coffee maker only con is that it\'s a little noisy and plastic cover came cracked. Had to exchange in store which defeated the purpose of buying online!'),
(8412, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-28', 'Love my Keurig I use my Keurig K250 daily and love it. It is easy to use, provides flavorful coffee, and the red color \"pops\" in my kitchen. I ordered my husband one for his office and it is the perfect size for his desk. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review\"'),
(8413, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-18', 'Love the new Keurig Overall it\'s a great brewer. I don\'t like that some of my old cups don\'t work even though they were purchased from Keurig.'),
(8414, 13, 2, 3, '2015-06-24', 'They don\'t make them like they use to. cheaply made compared to my old B60. that was a great machine. I hope this one lasts as long as our B60. did.'),
(8415, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-14', 'Great Brewer We use this every day. It\'s so nice to just get up on a morning , pop a pod in, cup on the tray and press the button, and a perfect cup of coffee is brewed in literally seconds. It looks good and doesn\'t take up room on my counter top . I love it !! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(8416, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-07', 'Worst purchase ever! By far the one of the worst purchases made!  This is my 3rd Keurig now (3rd unit being a warranty replacement).  1st old style unite was great but both 2.0 units pop the internal filter in k-cups and brew a cup full of grounds.  Such a waste of money.  Would not recommend buying.  Next unit will be a Ninja coffee bar.  Same features without the hassle'),
(8417, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-28', 'The worst brewer in America!!! My Keurig sounded like it was going to seriously self-destruct any second. I called and no one would upgrade my system knowing that this series are completely defected. They said that the order was already shipped when it wasn\'t. THEY LIE TO US BECAUSE THEY KNOW THIS PRODUCT BELONGS IN THE TRASH!!! SORRY BUT NOT SORRY. YOU MADE ME DO THIS.'),
(8418, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-29', 'A Must Have For Any Size Household This is such a great coffee maker. It doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space, which I love, it brews multiple size cups and it heats up rather quickly. It\'s the perfect size for home and office use.'),
(8419, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-27', 'Great Machine The product was smooth. The interface was easy to use. The coffee was dispensed at an quick rate making it also very efficient.'),
(8420, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-11', 'Perfect for city kitchens! The design of the Keruig 2.0 is perfect for those of us who have limited counter space (I have a tiny city apartment that won\'t accomodate larger machines). I also love the ability to brew only one cup at a time and the wide variety of flavor options -- even when I don\'t want coffee, I can still turn to my Keurig (the Mexican hot chocolate rocks!). Overall, I\'m super pleased with my machine!'),
(8421, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-27', '1 month later, doing great We have a couple of large keurigs at home. Bought this one for the office.- smaller/more compact. The maker is heavily used and after a month it is still working perfectly. I buy the k cups from the office supply guy and have not paid attention to the brands but there have been no issues. The maker came with a manual and easy to understand instructions.'),
(8422, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-12', 'Awesome machine for the price!! So this is my first Keurig purchase and I got it for a great price on Black Friday. I purchased the orange color one which is a pretty bright color. The coffee is amazingly hot! It does take a few minutes for the machine to warm up, but then once you place a Keurig cup in the machine it brews quickly.  If you purchase the regular Keruig cups the maximum size offered is 10 oz. So if you like more per serving you will have to purchase the K-mug. The machine reads the cups electronically, so you can\'t overide the size for the Keurig cups.   The other benefits to this maching is K-cafare option. You do have to purchase the pot separately (for $20),  but it is awesome feature if you are going to have company over.    I have been using the machine for only about 2 weeks, so I haven\'t had the opportunity to clean it. However, Keurig has conviently provided a special instrument to clean the needle in the machine.  I truly recommend this Keurig especially if you have never owned one. It has 3 features in one:  hot water dispenser, k-cup and k-carafe. You can\'t beat it for the price!!!'),
(8423, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-30', 'UHG !! This thing is terrible. Gimme my Bunn back. It makes the worst cup of coffee I ever tasted.'),
(8424, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Love it! I love my keurig 2.0 K250. It is super easy to use and the design fits perfect in my kitchen. So happy to have that many options for coffee and teas. The design of my brewer is elegant and neat at the same time. Having the option to brew one cup or a carafe makes me able to invite people over and avoid the waiting time of a regular coffee machine. Just love it! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review'),
(8425, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-11', 'I\'m in love!! I traded my old single cup keurig in for the 2.0 250, although I do like the look of the newer 250, I\'m in love with mine. I love that I can make a pot of coffee, drink one cup hot and then save it in the fridge for some iced coffee that afternoon. It is much faster than my old keurig and I love the setting adjustments so I can make my single cup nice and strong!! The only thing I don\'t like is that you do have to use branded coffee, I like to pick up extra pods when I see them on sale and they aren\'t always keurig brand.. I am still able to use it on my keurig at work, but would appreciate the freedom at home as well.'),
(8426, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-31', 'Great Purchase I\'m loving this Keurig! I wanted to upgrade from my Keurig Mini but not spend too much money and the K250 was definitely the right choice. It has a very sleek design that looks great in any setting. I got the black one to match the appliances in my kitchen and it looks great! It also has a water reservoir and more drink size options. Would definitely recommend.'),
(8427, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-27', 'new user\"I would buy this product again and again\" I am using it daily thanks to the extra Kcups included with my purchase. Can\'t wait to go shopping for more.'),
(8428, 14, 2, 4, '2015-02-24', 'Liked this item I was pleasantly surprised at the power of this blender. It chops, blends & liquifies anything. I got it at a great deal $24.99 (price cut). The glass blender jar makes it easy to clean and doesn\'t hold odors like the plastic ones.'),
(8429, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-12', 'Now fresher than ever! I have been using a Keurig brewer for a few years now and have always been satisfied with my original, older brewer. I was ecstatic once I received the 2.0- I have always been \"behind the times\" on technology, so this was a great chance to upgrade to a better Keurig system. I absolutely LOVE coffee, I can\'t get enough! Iced, hot, lattes, you name it, I\'ll drink it. My first impression of this system was how beautiful the design is! My other brewer had the water reservoir on the side, I love that this once has one on the back, and it\'s much larger, so I don\'t have to refill it after only a couple cups. I also love that the design fits in nicely with my other black kitchen appliances. Once out of the box, it was easy to assemble and get her all set up. This newer brewer doesn\'t have that plastic taste or smell from the factory like some of the older brewers do, so that is a plus! I popped in my first K-Cup and I was ready to enjoy a hot cup of delicious coffee! Since I had been using a Keurig for years, of course I had tons of K-Cups in stock. I ran into the problem with the new system not recognizing the older K-Cups. I think I heard there is a fitted piece you can install to get the Keurig to recognize the older cups, I haven\'t tried that yet. Honestly, this isn\'t a problem for me because there are so many cups available on the market. I did wish the box came with the carafe it boasts, Im not sure where to purchase the carafe or the K-Cups to use it, but I am definitely interested in trying that! I highly recommend this brewer to anyone who enjoys a fast on-the-run great cup of coffee, or to anyone who likes to sip while reading a good book. This brewer makes consistent, delicious coffee every single time, without fail.'),
(8430, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-28', 'Love it! I was nervous about my order after reading that it doesn\'t take all single serve coffee types but so far I have had no issues using my non \"official kcups\". Brews great coffee'),
(8431, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Fast Delivery I was very  pleased with the product. Fast delivery easy to use and beautiful color.'),
(8432, 13, 2, 2, '2016-08-06', 'Short life I bought the 200 model when it first came out but didn\'t use until 1 year ago. As of last week the heating element no longer heats. I have always used distilled water and maintained the brewer according to the directions. Bummer! I am now using my 2011 model individual brewer ag as in. It still works grest.'),
(8433, 13, 2, 3, '2017-01-03', 'Good to use I purchased it for my college daughter for her dorm. She told me it is good for her!'),
(8434, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-11', 'Love it I have been wanting one of these for a while and finally got. I am not a coffee drinker but I drink tea and apple cider. I love the convenience of using the Keurig versus going through the process of of making tea the regular way. Because of the Keurig and using K cups, I get to try different types of tea. It is quick, fast and easy clean up.'),
(8435, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'yummy treat Luv it,love it. Needed this maker asap and i got it at a great time and price'),
(8436, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-13', 'AMAZING I love that you can select if you\'d like your coffee brewed strong of normal. I like that you can select the cup size. AMAZING!'),
(8437, 13, 2, 1, '2016-08-03', 'Not so happy Loved the design. Loved the color. Loved the delicious coffee it brewed. There was a problem, however, and after 3 days of dealing with it, I had to take it back and exchange it for a Keurig Classic machine. I had owned a Classic and it gave me dependable service for about 3 1/2 years. I should have stuck with that model. With this new model, it seems about every 3rd or 4th cup we brewed, we not only got a cup of coffee, but we got a cup full of grounds spilling over from the K-Cup into our coffee. This was a brand new machine, and we read and followed the instruction booklet to the letter. We did not overfill the water tank. We tried securely placing the K-Cup into the holder, and we also tried just loosely placing the cup in the holder. Made no diference. We also used fresh filtered water. With each mishap, I disassembled and rinsed the cup holder, then ran a cleansing brew of plain water to make sure all grains were cleared. It never failed to happen again at some point, and after 3 frustrating mornings of dealing with it, I gave up and exchanged it out for the classic. I am hoping for a much better performance tomorrow morning.'),
(8438, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-24', 'My Little Sandy Pearl <3 Ive now had my Keurig for two weeks, and I LOVE IT! This is my first Keurig, but Ive used one before (my mother has had one for four or five years). Im a college student living at home, and I have to wake up very early in the morning, so Im usually in a hurry to get out the door. I have the Sandy Pearl color, and let me tell you, it looks absolutely beautiful in my room! (I love the ability to pick from many colors!) I wouldve chosen Turquoise, but Im hoping to take this with me to my apartment after I graduate, so I chose a neutral color. The heat up, in my opinion, is very quick. I plug my Keurig in, and it begins heating while I start getting ready. Once the sound stops, I put in my favorite cup or use a re-fillable cup and place a tea bag inside. There are many sizes and custom brewing options, which is great because I have so many different kinds of cups and mugs. Some only can hold 4-6oz. and others can hold 10oz. or more. I love the touch screenIts elegant AND easy! While heating and brewing make a decent amount of noise, its much quieter than the one my mother has. My little sisters room is adjacent to mine, and its never woke her up yet! The beverages are always extremely hot, which is great, considering that some days my cup sits there a while before Im ready to grab it, and I think that attributes to how well it brews bags of tea. Ive been pleasantly surprised with how much flavor of tea has made it into my mug without steeping. Now for the cons_ There arent many, but the ones it has, I feel, are pretty important. 1) Several of my travel mugs cannot fit under it (and yes, that is with the tray removed). My solution has been to place a different, smaller cup underneath the Keurig and transfer it into my travel cup afterwards. Its a nuisance, but it works. Luckily, for me, I dont use travel mugs every day, so its not that big of a deal. 2) Theres no auto-off feature. This is the biggest frustration for me. I have to unplug my Keurig after every use to conserve energy. One day I left it on and noticed it DID turn off, BUT then I did the same experiment two other days and it stayed on all day long_ (10+ hours) All in all, Im extremely satisfied with my purchase. The cons are nothing that cant be fixed with a few extra steps on my end, which in the end, doesnt matter as much. This little thing is still faster and easier than stopping by the coffee shop or boiling hot water on the stove for tea. Love this little gem!  **Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!**  (For those wondering about the free pods... Keurig sent me an email a couple weeks after registering my Keurig explaining this promotion. So don\'t forget to register!!)'),
(8439, 14, 2, 2, '2015-01-11', 'Not as functional as need be This blender takes a while to actually make a smoothie. It has difficulty chopping up certain items, such as apples, and requires a lot of manipulation. Also tried to make pesto with the blender, which Ive done with blenders far less \"impressive,\" and it was a complete fail. I will return this item and try another brand.'),
(8440, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-12', 'Ridiculous I LIVE for coffee, strong cup first thing, multiple cups throughout, adore the smell, the taste, the everything about it. I also live in an apartment with limited counter space, so when I purchased my Keurig Mini I was very excited. I LOVED my mini, have had it for YEARS, brewed a fantastic cup of coffee whenever I wanted it. My boyfriend moved in and we used the mini more often, and his travel mug is bigger so we used to brew two cups to fill it, he also likes a stronger brew, and well the mini - after years of use just didn\'t keep up and broke down (I think I actually shed a tear). So, we purchased a K250 - set it up, swapped the toaster oven for a toaster because of the space, and well ... it looks pretty. Despite the 9 brew sizes it claims to brew (HUGE draw to this machine), the bigger machine doesn\'t really brew anything more that the mini did. Evidently it\'s a standard 4 size (and the 10oz is actually less that the 10oz my mini brewed), it\'s not stronger, not even when you press the strong button, there\'s no auto shut off, additional 3 sizes are available but only if you buy the KMug (and only 9 varieties available), and the rest are for the carafe (but only for cup portions), so the 9 brew sizes aren\'t truly available... The strong brew tastes more like water poured over ground up beans than it does a good cup of coffee. We\'re waiting upwards of ten minutes for the machine to warm up each morning, and overall just disappointed. Worst money on a Keurig spent and zero benefits ...'),
(8441, 13, 2, 5, '2016-07-13', 'Love this Keurig!!!Beautiful to look at and brews great coffee.I had a smaller 1 cup before,this one is wonderful,the coffee tastes so good.Definitely a 5star. I had it ready in 5 minutes.'),
(8442, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-26', 'Perfect! Awesome!   Hot coffee fast.  Beautiful color and design.  Don\'t hesitate on this one!!'),
(8443, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-15', 'More Than One Cup, Yes Please I love my new Keurig 2.0 K250 Brewing System. I love the look with the water reserve located in the back. However, the reserve has no handle and is an awkward shape to hold. I always end up spilling water on the floor. I love the different size settings and the 4 cup carafe option. I frequently drink more than one cup on the weekends and days I work from home and this is an exciting feature for me. I also like the setting that I can make it stronger. This feature has been used often. Lastly, I don\'t like it has a filter that requires changes after a certain number of uses. I have a water filtration system on my refrigerator that I used with my old brewer and it worked just fine this way. Having to purchase these additional filters is an added expense I will have to figure out how to work into my budget.'),
(8444, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-10', 'In love with my Keurig! Ever since the first Keurig in my family home, I have been in love with the product. Easy to use, fast, some many flavors to try (more coming). It has been the best investment especially with myself moving out of my family home. My parents have the 550 brewer which works great and with the carafe option perfect for entertaining. I have the 250 which works for my, since I am on the go between work and social life. I work in NYC so you are always on the move and my Keurig works perfect with my busy life style. Happy Happy Happy Keurig owner, used everyday no matter what! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8445, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-13', 'Great Purchase I am very pleased with this Keurig Coffee Maker. It is very easy to use, and the coffee is just the right temperature. I shopped online for the best price and found it at Target.'),
(8446, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-15', 'I Totally Get the Hype I\'m an instant coffee drinker...well I was until I tasted coffee brewed w/a Keurig. It\'s like having a coffee house in my apartment. For so long I scoffed at my friends when they bragged about their Keurigs. Well, I\'ll be the first to say that I totally understand why Keurig has so many fans. I can\'t wait to try iced tea next.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8447, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Love it! This was my first coffee maker, I saw it on sale and I couldn\'t pass up! I\'ve had for 1 week now and it is amazing! It works wonderfully and I\'ve had any problems with it so far. One thing I will say is the Sandy Pearl color is GORGEOUS! I wanted a white and was upset it was outstock so I settled for the sandy pearl aand when it came in the mail I was soooo happy I didn\'t get white. This color is so pretty and it fits perfect in my white kitchen. Love it, one of the best purchases ever!'),
(8448, 13, 2, 1, '2016-06-03', 'Worst Brewer Ever! This is the worse brewer model ever! I say model because I have had 3 of the same. Keurig has sent me 2 replacements for the same exact problem. I have tried multiple different kinds of k cups (yes, they are Keurig approved), and keep getting the same results. A cup FULL of grounds. We just received our third brewer in the mail. We followed the directions to set it up. And same thing. Keurig assures me that it isn\'t the brewer, which I find hard to believe. A brand new brewer should work and have no issues.'),
(8449, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-01', 'Coffee maker second to none! This is my second one and I am sure it will not be my last. These coffee makers are the best.'),
(8450, 13, 2, 3, '2017-01-02', 'Nice coffee maker but read the fine print Nice coffee maker - they no make a newer model so this model will soon be old news. The box picture was a bit mis-leading since the box shows the carafe next to the coffee maker but does not come with this model. Sold separately in the fine print reading.'),
(8451, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-05', '5 stars! I got this as a Christmas present.. it is very efficient and easy to use!'),
(8452, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-26', 'Keurig 2.0 Rocks! Received this from my daughter & son-in-law for Christmas 2015. Absolutely the best coffee brewer that I have ever had. Easy setup and if you follow the instructions I am positive that you will get the most from this product.'),
(8453, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Keurig is Amazing! I use my Keurig every morning to make coffee quickly and quietly and throughout the day to make hot tea and hot cocoa. It brews fast and is relatively quiet. As a first time Keurig user, it is very easy to operate. The \"power off\" button on the touchscreen took a while to figure out because, the instructions don\'t tell you that you have to press and hold the button for it to actually turn off. Other than that this Keurig is amazing. Thank you Keurig for making such a creat machine.'),
(8454, 13, 2, 1, '2016-04-16', 'CUP FULL OF GROUNDS I HAVE HAD 3 BREWERS AND EACH LIFT A CUP FULL OF GROUNDS.I RETURNED THE FIRST ONE TO THE STORE AND HAD IT REPLACED,THE SECOND ONE DID THE SAME THING.I CALLED THE COMPANY AND THEY SENT ME ANOTHER ME ANOTHER ONE,IT DID THE SAME THING .IWAS ASSURED THE PODS WOULD BE OK TO USE.ON THE BOX IT SAID COULD BE USED IN ANY KEURIG BREWER.I HAVE CALLED 3 TIMES WITH NO POSITIVE RESULTS.IT IS GETTING VERY OLD NOT TO ABLE TO GET RESOLVED. TERRY CLARK'),
(8455, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-11', 'Great upgrade! I had a Keurig K45 Elite Brewing System previously before getting the 2.0 k250, so I was already a huge an of Keurig. Now i\'m an even bigger fan! This brewer provides the same great tasting, quick coffee has the original with added features. I love that I am able to make myself a personal cup of a carafe for guests.'),
(8456, 13, 2, 2, '2017-01-02', 'Keurig K200 This coffee maker leaks all over the place.  Bought the carafe, bought the carafe pod, worked once and the next pot leaked everywhere. No timer, coffee was weak with the first carafe that did work. Will be returning all items.'),
(8457, 14, 2, 5, '2015-12-15', 'Amazing blender on a budget! For those of you who are looking for an inexpensive blender, this one is the one for you! It blends really well, just make sure there is enough liquid in the pitcher to keep things moving. Also I really enjoy how the blender comes apart so you can wash the blade attachment well. The blender has lasted us about a year, so I think it is worth the small investment, especially if you would like to enjoy smoothies or a creamy soup as a college student. :)'),
(8458, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-22', 'How Did I Live Without This??! LOVE, LOVE, LOVE!!! I can brew a carafe of coffee and switch right to a cup of iced tea!! So fast and convenient it\'s not even funny. My husband uses this for coffee daily, I use it more casually for hot chocolate, iced tea, apple cider, etc...the variety of k-cups available are really amazing! It does ask for water quite frequently, but that\'s the only less than perfect statement I have about this product.'),
(8459, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-18', 'Piece of Trash. Don\'t waste your money. Shoddy product. This is the second unit that has failed after a few months. Thank goodness for warranties. I can\'t believe Keurig has put its name on such a terrible product. They should be ashamed. Do not buy this coffee maker. You will be sorry after a few months.'),
(8460, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'Great for an office Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8461, 13, 2, 4, '2016-02-21', 'Replacement 2.0 K500 This is a replacement for a Keurig 2.0 which started having problems with starting the brewing cycle-sometimes it would start and sometimes not. This warranty replacement is much noisier than any Keurig I have ever had but it brews well.'),
(8462, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-31', 'My first Keurig This is my first Keurig brewer. I love it. It is so easy to use. Great to have a fresh cup of coffee each time. I also used the Iced Tea pod. The tea is as good as the coffee. I highly recommend buying this brewer. You will not be disappointed! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review\"'),
(8463, 13, 2, 4, '2016-02-02', 'Great coffee maker I love this coffee maker just wish that it held more water in the reservoir. After an 8 oz cup the water goes from the maximum fill line to the minimum and I feel like I fill it daily'),
(8464, 13, 2, 2, '2016-10-05', 'Pods exploding We purchased this brewer because we absolutely loved our old Keurig that died after three years of fairly heavy use, and the old model was no longer available. I am not at all happy with this brewer because it does not work as well as our old one. This brewer does not work with about half of the k-cups that we have purchased. We get a \"pressure warning\" on some pods and others will simply blow to seal at the top of the pod and spray grounds all over. We have found some pods that work quite well but we are kind of stuck using one type of coffee.'),
(8465, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-09', 'Morning cup! Like the machine. Like the choice of colors. The price is way too expensive!!!!!!!!!'),
(8466, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Great Gift for my Grandfather I was worried the new 2.0 would be difficult for my grandfather to use, given that he is not a tech person and it uses touchscreens. However, it was simple enough that he has been using it without issue.'),
(8467, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'i love it glad i decided to order this. love everything about it. great price'),
(8468, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-27', 'sorry I spent the money Bought this for Christmas for myself. I loved the idea of having a large water reservoir.What I didn\'t know was a lot of my Keurig k cups would not work. Very disappointing for the cost of this machine and the cost of coffee. I wouldn\'t buy again.'),
(8469, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-11', 'Pros + Conts The Keurig 2.0 is DEFINITELY an update from the old-fashioned (haha) one. Here is a list of the pros (and very few cons) of the Keurig 2.0: Pros: Screen that tells you what is going on. This is AWESOME for someone who is impatient and skeptical, like me. If it weren\'t for the screen on the new Keurig 2.0 telling me that it was preheating, I might go into a panic, wondering if I did something wrong. And it is is touch screen. This is awesome. Water amount options. Via the touch screen you can select four (I think the old Keurig machines only had 3) different pour options: 4 oz (for super-strong), 6 oz, 8 oz, 10 oz. I, a coffee fiend, went for the strong-ish 6 oz pour. Add hot water option. Turns out that the 6 oz pour did not fill my mug enough, so I was was pleased that there was an option to add just hot water to your cup. Even after adding hot water my cup of coffee was still really good and strong. I was honestly impressed with the Keurig coffee. Descaling solution. The machine came with descaling solution, which is great because if you want your coffee machine to last, you need to descale it often. A bunch of free pods. The Keurig 2.0 came with a bunch (I think ~30) free pods in all different varieties. Very generous of them! My husband even tried the tea and liked it. Very sleek and compact. This machine looks great on the counter in our small, seminary-housing apartment. It fit in the place I usually keep my blender (which means it is very compact). It fit well below our cabinets, as well. Instruction manual in multiple languages and has lots of good info. Including giving you information about recycling K-cups. And_perhaps my favorite: it is polite. This Keurig is noticeably polite! It says \"Welcome\", \"Please\", \"Enjoy\"_ etc. Very polite programing, thank you very much. Less dishes. At the end of the day, all you have to clean is your mug. Cons: No Carafe. I was excited about the coffee pot feature of the Keurig 2.0, which will be great when we have guests over. However the Carafe is sold separately, which kind of disappointed me. Froze. Because it is now run by a more complicated computer (because of the touch screen, etc.) this means there is more room for bugs. My machine got caught in a loop and was stuck \"preheating\" for about 10 minutes before I realized it was not really preheating. At that point I unplugged the machine to give it a restart. When I plugged it back in it started reheating right away. So, as you can see, there are very few cons and lots of pros! I will consider giving this as a gift for some upcoming weddings! The product is great.'),
(8470, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-01', 'Keurig is FANTASTIC Every Morning'),
(8471, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-10', '\"I would buy this product again and again\" I have this coffeemaker in my cottage at the beach. It is perfect size for how we use'),
(8472, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-08', 'Coffee lovers brewer I replaced my old Keurig with this model and I love it so much more. Even though I only brew one cup a day, I love the convenience of the water reservoir. It also has a nice, clean look. I\'ve been having none of the trouble I had with my old single brewer. No grounds in the cup! It makes a weird noise when brewing but the result is so good I don\'t mind. I also love being able to select strong brewing and cup size. I only wish you could have a 12 oz. cup. Thanks, Keuring, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8473, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-29', 'A great addition to your morning! I use this every morning and i love how fast and easy it is to use. just a few clicks and i\'ve got nice hot coffee! with other coffee makers, the coffee is never hot enough, but this is great. the only thing is the price. it\'s not something YOU NEED. but it is definitely nice to have if you can afford it!'),
(8474, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Great value Have 4 of them in different colors- for work and different rooms of the house!!'),
(8475, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-14', 'don,t judge a book by its cover eay to use/makes excellent coffee and ice tea'),
(8476, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-15', 'Awesome I have wanted to replace your ld Keurig for a while. I was dead set on the K450,but then I saw the size and color options of the 200. I don\'t have much counter space and my hubby doesn\'t drink coffee so the smaller model was perfect. My only complainthe is that it\'s a it noisy but not insanely loud.  Overall I love it and recomend it.'),
(8477, 13, 2, 4, '2016-10-03', 'Great machine with many options I love my new brewer and enjoy all of the different options and settings.  I also love the color options!  The sandy color looks great in my kitchen.  My only reason for giving 4 stars is that I wish it came with the carafe.  I\'d rather pay a little more and have everything in the box instead of shopping for it separately.'),
(8478, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-25', 'Wake Up & Smell the Keurig! I love coffee...all day, everyday. I fell in love with Keurig from my very first brewer and am now spoiled. The new K250 takes the cake! It is the easiest brewer to use, it offers so many cup sizes (including the carafe size), it is touch screen, and the water reservoir is huge! I love it so much!!! The only down side I have noticed, and it is so minor, is that it does not automatically shut off. Other than that tiny detail, this brewer has no flaws. I really love telling everyone that my Keurig brewer has a touch screen.'),
(8479, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-30', 'LOVE IT!!!!!!! This is my second Keurig. I tried to go back to a regular coffee brewer after my first Keurig needed to be replaced after 5 years of constant use..... and I lasted a few months. I really missed having a Keurig! I purchased the Keurig K200 in Sandy Pearl yesterday and absolutely love it. It is smaller and less bulky than my 2010 machine. Set up was a snap! Love the touch screen and water reservoir. If you use filtered water from your refrigerator, the reservoir fits easily in the water niche and doesn\'t take long to fill. Overall I am thrilled with this machine. Welcome back, Keurig!!!'),
(8480, 13, 2, 4, '2015-10-27', 'Love Love Love I find it eSY TO USE. i LIKED IT SO MUCH i* ORDERED ONE FOR MY SON AND HIS WIFE. tHE PRICE IS GREAT AND i LOVE THE FREE SHIPPING. i ALSO USED MY kEURIQ POINTS TO LOWER THE PRICE.'),
(8481, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-09', 'Perfect! I love this keurig! It replaced my old keurig and it is such a great upgrade. The machine itself is sleeker and has a touch screen. And the water reservoir is so great- the filter is easy to replace and has a date reminder that tells you when to replace the filter. Definitely recommend!'),
(8482, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-15', 'Great Coffee I absolutely love this Keurig. It makes great coffee. Most of the time, I say #HelloKeurig by using one K-Cup but make 16 ounces out of it. That makes the perfect strength coffee for me. The only downfall is that you have to buy certain k-cups. You can\'t buy the refillable one to use. My favorite thing about this machine is how quickly it heats up. It definitely is a time saver!'),
(8483, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-18', 'Was called the K250,now called K2.0-WHY THE CHANGE When I first bought this it was called the K250 but now is no longer shown. Now it\'s called the K2o. It is cheaply made. This is my 3rd replacement in less than 3 months. Pieces were missing in the 1st two and now I\'m waiting for the 3rd to arrive however no longer available in the color I originally orddered so stuck with ugly colors to coose from. Also was not offered the decals it shows with the machine. Have had nothing but problemd due to poor craftsmenship. It\'s loud, takes a long time to preheat, constantly have to clean it. I don\'t have anything good to say about this product except they\'re replacing the former ones I\'ve had problems with but still have not been offered any type of special compensations for all the problems I\'ve had with these machines. Would not recommend ordering this machine.'),
(8484, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-22', 'Why didn\'t I do this sooner? I can honestly say that this purchase has been life changing.  It is so convenient and wonderful.  My early mornings are so much easier.  I absolutely love anything that significantly eases my life, reduces time, stress, etc., and this fits the bill.  We also love it for hot chocolate that is always perfect.  I have never had a Keurig so I can\'t give a comparison of one model to the next, but I appreciate that it has the water storage so I would recommend this model rather than one that requires water each time.'),
(8485, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-11', 'Nor what I expected If you love a good brewed cup of coffee  this is NOT the machine to use. The coffee taste like instant coffee.'),
(8486, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Wonderful way to engage employees..... Thanks Keurig for being able to share my love of coffee & tea with my employees! I have owned several different Keurigs throughout the years. Reciently I purchased the Keurig 2.0 to keep in my office. It has been fun trying new types and brands of coffees and teas. I am now able to offer my employees drinks during company meetings at any time of the day. My Keurig is always for available to my employees to use, which allows for better communication throughout the day. This Keurig a great way to engage employees and have an open door policy!! It has been the best Human Resource investment that I have ever made!! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8487, 13, 2, 1, '2017-01-18', 'Don\'t waste your money Returned it after two days.  It doesn\'t produce a hot cup of coffee, only warm.'),
(8488, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'I love my Keurig This is my first Keurig - I love that everyone can have a different flavor coffee without making several pots. My hubby can have strong coffee and I can have regular, so we are both happy. It\'s also great that you can make 4, 6, 8 or 10 ounce cups of coffee for people who want more or less coffee. It is smaller than my old Mr. Coffee coffeemaker and has so many more options. I\'ll never go back to the old coffeemaker!'),
(8489, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-17', 'Kuerig 2.0 k200 Just got this model from target online in white and I\'m really pleased with how it looks and how it works ..... A great cup everyone ......so long drip pot hello to my new kuerig'),
(8490, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'LOVE my new 2.0! I love love love my new Keurig 2.0 K250! The carafe and carafe cups are an awesome and much needed addition to the regular single size brewing! I am saving so much money by skipping my daily coffee shop runs and making coffee at home! I literally use this machine daily, multiple times per day, for coffee, tea, cocoa, or just hot water! I could\'t do without it! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8491, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'we think we got a great deal our Keurig came to our door with the greatest of ease at a great price in a desired color...in the busiest shopping period of the year..Target really came through for us..:>)'),
(8492, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-23', 'Great Upgrade! I was afraid to change the machine I had but wanted one for school.  So I went for it and I love this model!  Very easy to use and I look the thinner look.'),
(8493, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-01', 'Great coffee brewer! I love having a fresh hot cup of coffee each day. I usually have two cups before noon. I do not understand the negative reviews, as my Keurig 2.0 has worked flawlessly for the 8 months that I have owned it so far. Just follow the instructions for proper cleaning and maintenance of the unit!'),
(8494, 13, 2, 2, '2015-07-11', 'Not a happy camper here!! First one I had to return because it was defective. Second one can\'t use the 10 oz. for coffee; you get a lot of grounds. Next time I\'m going to try a different brand. Cost way too much to not do what it says it does.'),
(8495, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'LOVE IT! I am a college student, spending lots on money on outside coffee shops, like Starbucks. I noticed that I was spending a great amount on money that I did not have. I then decided to research Keurigs. I wanted something convenient for me, something that would not take up a lot of space and that was affordable. After my research, I liked the K200 series, it was smaller, cute, and afforfable, and it gave me different color options to choose from. So far, I love it, I do not regret getting it. I live at home, and my mom is loving it as well. It is fast and convenient. I do not have to wait long to get my coffee. Also, I am not giving up my Starbucks, they have caramel flavored Starbucks K-Cups!'),
(8496, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-12', 'Great coffee maker, serves hot coffee, easy cleaing'),
(8497, 13, 2, 2, '2015-05-21', 'Not compatible with all k-cups This brewer is great, in theory. I have been trying to use it for all different brands and drinks available in k-cup form. The My K-cup does not work. Dark roast Newman\'s own doesn\'t work. Starbucks Verona blend doesn\'t work. Snapple iced teas don\'t work. I am pretty disappointed that I need to keep an old keurig around when I have such a gorgeous, fast, convenient machine.'),
(8498, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-18', 'Love This Brewer! I love my new Keurig! I\'ve owned a Keurig since they came out and I had used mine for a few years and decided it was time for a new one. I purchased this one and so far have had no issues, except that you can\'t turn off the LCD screen. It doesn\'t even dim which bothers me. However, other than that it\'s super easy to make coffee, and it comes out tasting great every time!'),
(8499, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-20', 'First Timer First Keurig I have used and love it.  Not a coffee drinker but love hot chocolate and tea.  Thanks Keurig!'),
(8500, 13, 2, 3, '2016-02-05', 'Just OK This one was a gift. I loved my old Keurig. I definitely would not have chosen this model. You cannot program it. So, every morning you have to turn it on to have the water heated. Looks good. Small footprint on the counter. Great colors.'),
(8501, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Best coffeemaker I usually use the brewer when I come home from work but I am looking forward to purchasing some K-mugs to brew a larger size to take to work. I have used a Keurig brewer since 2009. These new machines are much quieter and are very easy to use. The ability to brew 3-4 cups at once is awesome. I wish I had bought the next brewer up such as the k300 for the larger reservior and thr auto - off feature. I have received compensation/free product for my unbiased review.'),
(8502, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-03', 'K250 Brewing System Like this better than my K75.'),
(8503, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-17', 'i like it easy to use. makes good cup of coffee. can use regular coffee with a filter.'),
(8504, 13, 2, 5, '2016-05-05', 'LOVE IT!! First time to own one. Easy setup! Didn\'t realize it would make so many different sizes. It knows when you have the bigger cups, or smaller cups. It automatically puts it on the screen of your available choices, and it\'s a Touch Screen!! Love it!'),
(8505, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-25', 'Shipping fail This item was supposed to be delivered already, but has yet to arrive. It was a Christmas gift. It is disappointing that the date would be guaranteed and then delayed.'),
(8506, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-22', 'I love it, and I highly recommend it!! I love this coffee maker, I got the sandy pearl color is beautiful, very compact yet has a water reservoir, digital and easy to use, heats up water fast.\" I use it every day.'),
(8507, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-23', 'Coffee on a whole new level I received my Keurig in the mail today and was blown away by the sleek and modern design. I loved how much water it holds to make for quick and easy drinks without having to refill the water constantly. It is so easy to use/easy clean up/ quick and mess free. I would definitely recommend! The color selection is pretty neat as well.'),
(8508, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-21', 'Great Upgrade! I had a Keurig K45 Elite before receiving the 2.0 K250, so I was already a huge fan. Now, I am an even bigger fan! This brewer provides the same great tasting, easy to make coffee as the original with added features. My favorite is that I can make a personal cup for myself or a carafe for guests.'),
(8509, 13, 2, 1, '2015-07-08', 'Very bad... Received it Monday. Hooked it up yesterday and brewed two cups without any problem. Today it didnt recognize three K-Cups (which went to waste) and has been warming up now for 30minutes... It doesnt work!'),
(8510, 13, 2, 3, '2015-08-07', 'Keurig 2.0 K250 As I mentioned above, the stability of the machine is not great. It rocks back and forth everytime I push the button or lift up the handle. The water reservoir is not very convenient. If I were to do it over again, I would probably buy the K350 style. Other than that I love the machine. I am the only coffee drinker in my house, so it allows me to drink my coffee without having to brew a whole pot. The interaction I have had with Keurig has been great. Their service is wonderful. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8511, 13, 2, 1, '2016-07-08', 'Poor Performance I am on my second K 2.0 Brewer and both have had issues with over-pressured pods, which causes an extremely large mess before I leave for work pretty consistently. I dread making my coffee every morning, wondering if it will explode today. I had the same issue with the first, which Keurig graciously replaced, but the same issues continue with the new one. I think that there is a product flaw with this particular model.   I do however, have the Classic Mini Keurig  for at work and LOVE it. I have never had an issue with it.'),
(8512, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-22', 'Coffee Coffee Coffee! This Keurig is great. It\'s quiet, smaller and sleeker than other versions of the coffee maker, and makes a great cup of coffee every time! The water system seems improved and also easier to clean. The touchscreen is really great, and it\'s so easy to use. I don\'t like that I can only make up to 10oz. I used to have another Keruig that made 12-14oz (travel sizes). I wish it came with the K-Carafe. I think it\'s odd that it doesn\'t. But I do like the fact that I get a quick easy good cup of coffee in just a min or two and how it doesn\'t take up my entire counter! Totally worth it!'),
(8513, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-23', 'Love it! I am so happy with my purchase. I have wanted a Keurig for awhile and finally purchased once I found a good sale.  Love the color, love the touch screen, love the different size choices, love that I can dispense hot water for tea.  Don\'t love that I have to purchase 3 different pods if I want to use the caraf the travel mug and the mug. I would have liked a reusable pod for the caraf option at least. It doesn\'t come with any reusable pod. I would be a little disappointed if I paid full price.  Overall I\'m so glad I have a cute teal keurig.'),
(8514, 13, 2, 4, '2016-09-13', 'Love our new Keurig! Bought our new Keurig a few weeks ago and am enjoying the convenience and exploring some different coffees. Found that adding an ounce or two of water to a larger cup and brewing on strong I can get a little larger serving if needed. Only downside is the Keurig is kind of noisy. I guess that\'s normal. Recommend the unit highly.'),
(8515, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Keurig is awesome! I got my Keurig at an amazing price!!!! I love it. It is so easy to use! Love all its features. Love the color!'),
(8516, 13, 2, 1, '2016-08-09', 'Rosemary I had the original Keurig.  This one was a pain in the neck to install because of its cheasy plastic partis.  Will return it.  First one delivered the plastic was already all broken.  Should have taken that as a warning!'),
(8517, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Love it The only bad thing about this Keurig is the design of the water tank. It\'s on the backside of the unit. So I have to pull it out from under the cabinet in order to refill it with water. It\'s just a small inconvenience. The great thing I love is the color-I got the Peacock Blue- and this is such an easy to use unit. my 8 year old loves to make his own hot chocolate with. It\'s a nice upgrade from the original series I had. Getting it on a Black Friday deal wasn\'t so bad either!'),
(8518, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-15', 'Must Have This is the first brewer that I own and I am extremely happy with it. I have limited counter space and its size is just perfect for that. It is relatively easy to use, and straightforward. I love that everyone in my family can brew their own individual cups with ease. Plus, it is a time saver within a minute or two your drink is ready. However, the small reservoir holds enough to brew only three 10oz cups, or one carafe. If you have guests over, or are hosting a breakfast be prepared to refill quite a few times. Other than that it is great every day product to have.'),
(8519, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-10', 'Not Good! I currently have a Keurig. I bought this model because of the color.....had to return it. It is very noisy! Keurig you dropped the ball on this one. It also seems to be more cheaply made than your other models.'),
(8520, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Great brewer at a great price. Bought this to replace a Tassimo that died less than one year after obtaining it. So far I like this brewer a lot. Very easy to use and to adjust the brew quality. Also easy to clean. Wish the water reservoir were a little larger. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8521, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-07', 'Love my Keurig 2.0 This is our second Keurig 2.0. We bought this one to use in our RV. Easy and quick. Love it! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8522, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Great Coffee Maker This was my first Keurig purchase and I am very pleased with this brewer. It takes about 3 minutes to make a cup of coffee which is great and very easy to use. It has a touch screen that gives you directions and the ability to control the strength of the coffee. This is a great coffee make and I would recommend it to anyone who enjoys a great cup of coffee. Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review!!!'),
(8523, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-09', 'Love my Keurig Great product and value.  I use mine multiple time everyday.  Have purchased several for family and friends.'),
(8524, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Why did I wait so long ? This is my first Keurig and I love this little wonder . It makes the perfect cup of coffee every time . It is so easy to use , and to clean . I am truly enjoying this machine . I ordered it when it was 30% off and got free shipping to boot . Why did I wait so long to take a chance on this delightful appliance ?'),
(8525, 13, 2, 4, '2015-11-11', 'Love my Keurig 2.0 I use my Keurig 2.0 EVERYDAY! and always wandered when I place a store bought K-cup or even my own K-cup I only have 3 choices in ounces. It always starts with 8 oz and then I can select the other ounces which are 6 oz & 4 oz. This upsets me because I have a favorite coffee mug which is kind of big, so when I select the only big ounce size (8 oz) when I look in my cup I feel like I have to repeat step 1 again. Then I went on Keurig\'s website and it says for the 2.0 it has more than 3 settings?? is my Keurig 2.0 broke or something? I plan on buying the carafe but sometimes I just want one big cup of coffee. Can somebody from the Keurig Corp. tell me why I only have 3 different ounce settings? maybe something needs to be replaced? Thank You!'),
(8526, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-11', 'Love My New Keurig 2.0 Very pleased with both performance and taste. I use my new Keurig 2.0 mainly for single 8oz. cups. I do not care that the maker uses only Keurig pods with readable lids, as that is all I utilize. I do not use ground coffee in a reusable generic K-cup. My last Keurig lasted several years (much longer than any of my old Mr. Coffee machines). Would recommend to anyone.'),
(8527, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-15', 'Great product but be careful .... Keurig has now installed an \"eye\" which can tell if you are using their exclusive products in their machine or not. My husband and I are used to using Cameron\'s Coffee products. We soon found out that we could not use their k-cups in this machine because the packaging did not have an outside ring in the printing on the k-cup that showed a Keurig cup design. Once we found out the go around on that, we are able to use the machine and it works wonderfully!! We couldn\'t be happier. The whole reason for us getting this machine is that our other Mr. Coffee brand Keurig had stopped working. We are VERY happy with this machine. The water warms up almost right away.'),
(8528, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-11', 'Love my keurig! I got my keurig for christmas, not the color I wanted so I had to exchange it. None of the local stores had the color I wanted but everyone was so helpful in helping me order it. The keurig was very quick and easy to set up and it works perfectly!'),
(8529, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-18', 'Brew your coffee within seconds Great brewer. The brewer itself is light but I\'m sure its not portable.  Great look in the kitchen.  Not as loud as the older one I had.  It\'s a little odd the water reservoir is at the back since I\'m used to it being at the side which was easier to fill up with water . But that\'s what makes it sleeker in its design.  I used to be able to place it underneath my cupboard . Once you turn on the k200 it brews hot coffee then when you are done with that cup it heats up the water for the next brew which is the part that I don\'t really like . The brewer stays on and I wouldnt use it until the next few hours. Once I do brew a cup it wouldn\'t brew the coffee as hot. But it\'s not so much a big deal. I still enjoy my coffee . K200 only takes k-cups that are only Keurig seal approved . But it would make sense to just purchase a refillable k-cup accessory and it will make life well . I\'d totally recommend K200'),
(8530, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-07', 'My newest baby I absolutely love my Keurig. I got it for Christmas and it\'s amazing. It was very easy to assemble, it came with very clear directions, and and it also included a filter.'),
(8531, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-23', 'LOVE THIS KEURIG I use this product everyday to make tea or hot coco. I am a college student, so it is very easy putting a pod in and getting my drinks to go! I recommend this to any college student looking for drinks that are high in sugar or just want a simple drink to go.'),
(8532, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-05', '\"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\" I am very happy with my Keurig K250. I am not a big coffee drinker. I do drink tea and I love it. Best purchase I made this year. It\'s very stylish! Love the look!'),
(8533, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-12', 'In love with my first Keurig!! I use my beautiful new Keurig 2.0 k250 everyday, sometimes multiple times a day. My drink of choice is the sweet and creamy donut house brew over ice (so good). This is my first Keurig, as I was always skeptical about brewing just 1 cup in a limited size. I previously used a traditional coffee maker to make a pot at a time. I was very impressed that I am able to fit my tall 24oz tumbler without issue and my even larger 32oz mason jar style tumbler with a little modification. I have not yet purchased the carafe, but I plan to do so in future for when we have company. Although, we had several guests over and I made 5 individual cups in a row and the machine never skipped a beat! And so fast too!! The 40oz water resevior is great! I would say the only con for me, is that I was expecting it to be a little more compact. The design is very sleek, and the machine is narrow, but I still feel it takes up as much room as a traditional brewer. We have a very small kitchen, so my K250 currently resides on a shelving unit rather than the counter. It is a great product I have and would continue to recommend to a friend.'),
(8534, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-21', 'I am really satisfied with my purchase. I was able to get it when it was on sale for $59.99 plus a $15 gift card. At first I was doubtful of the purchase not because of the machine but because I didn\'t want to be buying the expensive keurig k cups. Luckily I found k cups that work with machine at ALDI. These k cups from Aldi are less than $4 for 12 k cups and there are in different flavors like Colombian, donut store, breakfast blend, etc. I also bought a reusable cup to put in my coffee but I would just rather pop a k cup. By using the k cups from ALDI I don\'t worry about making a mess or cleaning the reusable k cup, just insert, brew and toss the k cups.'),
(8535, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-23', 'Great coffee maker I received the coffee maker so fast, easy to use, great value for the price. easy to clean and set up, i really love this item'),
(8536, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-13', 'Great Machine I upgraded from a 1.0 Mini and the K250 has been truly impressive so far. I use it everyday and so far it stays pretty clean (it even comes with cleaner for later on) and I don\'t have to worry about cleaning out gunk from the spout to get CLEAR, hot water if I choose to have tea instead of coffee. It does take a few moments to heat up, but it\'s relatively quiet and produces a steady stream of beverage. The only things I don\'t care for is there are only two cup size options (4 oz and 6 oz) for the hot water, yet there are three sizes for K-cup pods (6 oz, 8 oz, and 10 oz). If I want 10 oz of water, I have to run both the 4 oz and the 6 oz. Also, sometimes it doesn\'t fill the mug as much as I think it should. I appreciate the color choices as well as the extras included. All things considered, I\'d recommend this to anyone! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8537, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-22', 'too good not to share !!! i use this keurig 2.0 everyday for coffee and tea absolutley love it, its supose to be a compact one but still seems bulky to me but still great makes the perfect cup everytime !!! the only thing i dont like is the price of the kcups and you dont get that many in a box if they would add more to the kcups price would be ok but i do still love this keurig i would diff recomend tthis one !!'),
(8538, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-12', 'Won\'t accept all k-cups I am losing money on already purchased k-kups from brands offered on the Keurig website. (eg:Cafe Express, Tazo tea) My Keurig 2.0 K200 refuses to brew them and gives me an error message after all the holes are punched in them. The Keurig logo is on all of these k-kups. I\'m not happy.'),
(8539, 14, 2, 4, '2015-05-01', 'nice blender wonderful blender I like the two tone color'),
(8540, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-14', 'LOVE THIS BREWER! Originally I purchased this to take RV\'ing, but quickly moved it to my kitchen to use daily! I love the K250 and have already recommended it to my friends. It\'s fast, easy, compact and holds a lot of water for its size. I also love it\'s versatility in working with the K-cup, K-mug, or K-carafe. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8541, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-07', 'Are you kidding? This brewer was sent to me as a replacement for a brewer that had stopped working. The company rep whom I dealt with was wonderful, and the new brewer was here in two days. Now for the bad news. The replacement brewer is spewing grounds all over the counter top and also onto the floor. It resembles a volcanic eruption. I\'ve been a Keurig user for years and am using the product as directed. Never have I dealt with anything like this! I\'m ditching the replacement and going back to a traditional coffee pot. Keurig, get your act together.'),
(8542, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-10', 'Oasis Keurig I bought this Keurig on sale to replace my old one and the color is amazing.  It looks so beautiful sitting on my counter and I have already used it twice and the new slim design is perfect!'),
(8543, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-29', 'very nice This is great! Heats up in about one and a half minutes. Looks sleek and nice on my counter. You can brew different sizes and strengths. Only con: it said preheating and i tried everything in the manual to find what was wrong because it wouldn\'t do anything. After looking online I saw that the needle that pokes the top of the pod sometimes gets clogged ( this happened after 12 or so brews). I just unplugged the machine and stuck a paperclip (clean) into the needle and it has worked fine ever since.'),
(8544, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-25', 'Best Gift Ever THIS WAS A GIFT. BEST GIFT I COULD GET. DID WHAT IT SAID IT WOULD DO. I USED IT SO MUCH IT DIED. I CRIED AND SAID NOW WHAT. WHERE CAN I GET MY COFFEE. MY BROTHER WAS REAL NICE GIVING ME THIS. WISH IT WAS COLORED BACK THEN, I LOVE BLUE. MISS MY COFFEE.'),
(8545, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-22', 'Pod Disappointment! We purchased the K250 specifically because of the option to use the K MUG pods that could brew larger cup sizes.  I am a tea drinker and now have learned that teas are not offered in the MUG size. The K250 model is easy to use but if in the end I\'m not getting the cup of tea I was hoping for or am going to have to use 2 pods, what is the point? Disappointed!!'),
(8546, 13, 2, 4, '2015-10-31', 'K250 Rating: B Good for quick morning coffee Home user'),
(8547, 13, 2, 2, '2016-01-04', 'A Christmas Mess I got this for Christmas from my mother, she ordered it in Nov and it just came today Jan 4. I cannot even register it and I am thinking of putting it back in the box and sending it back it is too much work and too many parts and solutions. The serial number does not even register, nice thought from mom, but it cost too much to have to keep buying, I can use a regular machine.'),
(8548, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Perfect for College! I bought this product to use in my dorm room for college and I absolutely love it! This product is very easy to use and will give you all the directions you need to know right on the screen. Coffee making is easy and fast which is a plus when I\'m rushing to get to class in the morning. I use this product everyday and it\'s working perfectly! Overall, I really love this coffee maker! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8549, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-10', 'Awesome Overall, this is a great product! This is my first Keurig, so I wasn\'t sure what to expect. I love that it\'s stylish, perfectly sized, and FAST! One disappointment is that a bigger brew size tends to result in slightly weaker coffee. It\'s awesome for a quick cup, especially when you don\'t want to make a full pot! This would be great at work when the mood strikes for a caffeine boost.'),
(8550, 13, 2, 3, '2015-05-07', 'awesome! love the product. hate that it will only use keurig brand cups and no other ones.'),
(8551, 13, 2, 2, '2015-09-02', 'Feeling Scammed- Didn\'t get even one cup I was very disappointed once I had purchased the beautiful red Keurig I was unable to even make one cup of coffee. I made this purchase to replace my family member\'s Keurig which no longer works consistently or not at all. Once I got it and set it up and was ready to to make a cup of coffee I found out it will only accept Keurig brand pods. This is not acceptable because so many companies make cups that fit the original one. I returned it immediately to get my money back. Very disappointed.'),
(8552, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-15', 'Smaller size, but not lacking I received the Keurig 2.0 K200 thanks to influenster, One of the best things of the Keurig 2.0 K200 is it\'s size, it easily fits just about anywhere with ease. You might think with a smaller brewing system the coffee wouldn\'t be as great, but it\'s amazing! Absolutely nothing has been left out of this brewing system. Setting upmy Keurig quick, easy, and simple.'),
(8553, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-04', 'One of our favorites of the four we have purchased My husband and I would be lost without a Keurig period. We put away our limited edition one when we purchased this one. My husband has become more picky than me, and that\'s a difficult thing to accomplish. Practically runs in the door after work and MUST start a cup immediately, same in the morning. Only one we purchase now is The Donut Shop!!! Love these machines. Could never go back to coffee sitting on a plate not knowing if s cold or burnt.'),
(8554, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-20', 'Colors even though it is listed a white, it is more an ivory color than pure white.'),
(8555, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Fills the bill for my needs Thought I would never buy a Keurig coffee maker but I couldn\'t resist this deal.  It\'s the easiest to use of any of many coffee makers I have had over the years.  I use an \"Ecobrew\" that lets me make from 1-6 cups and that saves me money.  Glad I have it.'),
(8556, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-24', 'Love the Keurig 2.0! Love this product, thought it was AMAZING! So easy to use, great coffee in seconds!'),
(8557, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-09', 'Love the size and function of this Keurig I love the size and function, I used to have a mini because the regular was way too big for my counter, but was missing out on having a water reservour. This is definitely a perfect fit for me and my family. Thank, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8558, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-20', 'Perfect Sleek New Brewer I am an everyday coffee drinker and the new Keurig 2.0 K250 is perfect whether you drink coffee daily or just want it once in awhile. The updated design is perfect for any home or office setting and having 9 sizes allows everyone to be satisfied with the perfect amount of coffee or tea. I love that a filtered watering system was added and it makes me feel much better when drinking my coffee in the morning. Overall the product works great, it cost effective, and nothing is better than the smell of fresh coffee in the morning!'),
(8559, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-20', 'Must have if you love coffee It is about 2 weeks since I bought a Keurig K200 coffee maker and I love it. I have been using a Black & Decker drip coffee maker for the past couple of years and upgrading to K200 was an excellent choice in my case. The coffee brewed by this machine is comparable to the ones in the coffee shop. One drawback back though is the machine does not auto power off, which in my view is bit annoying.'),
(8560, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Compact Keurig 2.0 This is a compact Keurig 2.0 K200,  is nice because it doesn\'t take up a lot of space on the counter.  I also have a larger Keurig which is better if you are drinking lots of coffee since you don\'t need to fill the water compartment as often.  I like this K200 for me because I usually only make one cup in the morning and one in the evening. It\'s also nice because you can brew hot water and use it for your regular tea bags.'),
(8561, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Love my new brewer I\'ve been a Keurig user for several years now and this new brewer doesn\'t disappoint! It was very easy to set up and start brewing my first cup. A few of the reviews I read before ordering the 2.0 K250 indicated it was noisy during the brewing process. I didn\'t find it to be noisy at all. Refilling the water container is easy and I like that it is positioned on the back of the brewer instead of the side, which leaves a bit more room on the counter. I also like the fact that there are several choices for the size of cup you want to brew. I\'ve only been using this new brewer for a few weeks, but so far I\'m very pleased with its performance. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8562, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-18', 'K200 disappointing I waited for years to buy a Keurig, only to return in less than a week. Drink coffee every day and very disappointed this machine is not at all what I hoped. Not sure I will try different model.'),
(8563, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-15', 'Makes a quick cup of coffee The Keurig makes a quick cup of coffee which is really nice for a quick out the door morning. Haven\'t tried the K Carafe pods yet but will try them soon. However be aware that some of the reusable k cups don\'t really fit that well and make a little bit of a gritty cup of coffee. I also love the product to make hot water for tea!  ps \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(8564, 13, 2, 2, '2015-10-14', 'New K200 is disappointing Love Green Mountain coffee and miss my old Keurig machine after many years of service. New K 200 unfortunately makes very weak coffee [more like tea] Hope I can find a resolve'),
(8565, 14, 2, 5, '2015-12-11', 'excelant blender perfect price This blender is perfect, bought it to be gift for christmas, perfect price, perfect gift.'),
(8566, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'Great brewer for great price First Keurig purchase and very happy with the product. I\'ve used other Keurig machines at the office and this one is not as bulky as other models and makes a great cup of coffee after every brew. I use a few times a week and is perfect for my needs. Just a few minor personal preferences that are missing, like auto-off function, having to manually press the touch screen to power off makes me feel the touchscreen may eventually go bad, but only time will tell. Also the water reservoir requires to be filled to a minimum and for my frequency of use, water sits for a few days until next use. But overall a great product for a great price, would definitely recommend this brewer. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(8567, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-11', 'Nice Model! This is a nice, no fluff, no frills model.  It brews cups, mugs, and carafes (but you have to buy separate pods for the mugs and carafes) with a small amount fo space for limited counter space in a tiny apartment kitchen.  You do have to fill the water tank more often if you brew more than two cups a day, since it it a smaller model.  But overall it works great for a couple.'),
(8568, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-07', 'Tidy, simple, convenient! Tidy, simple, and convenient! Multiple colors available to match your kitchen. \"Strong\" option allows you to brew a stronger cup if you\'d like. Brews the perfect cup or carafe in no time. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8569, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-13', 'Pros and Cons I like the ability to select brew size and strength on the is model, but it\'s much noiser than my old Keurig brewer was.'),
(8570, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-19', 'Love it! Got this as a gift for my husband. Very easy to use/clean. Beautiful color :D Absolutely love it!'),
(8571, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Love My K250 I am excited about my new Keurig and have loved trying out the different flavors and varieties of tea and coffee. My daughter and I both use it daily and find that it is wonderful. Thank you.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8572, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-11', 'Awesome Brewer! This is my first Keurig and I must say_I am in LOVE! Setup was easy. The screen tells you everything you need to know to operate it. It\'s quick and efficient. Never would I have imagined that I would find a brewer that I absolutely love. Early mornings are made easier with just the touch of a button.'),
(8573, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-28', 'Awesomeness Awesomeness Exponentially'),
(8574, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-21', 'very disappointing I purchased Kuerig coffee pots for all of our children and they loved them so decided to get one for my husbands birthday. I bought tbe K200 from Walmart because of the compact size and we have a small kitchen. The first few cups of coffee were good but within days we had so many grounds we couldnt drink it. Took it back and exchanged ut but had the same problem immediately. This time we called Kuerig and they agreed to replace the pot. We received the new pot todat (our 3rd) and we still get grinds. Called customer service and they are sending us another pot (#4) however i would prefer a refund but since we didnt but it from their website they cannot give us a refund. I wish we had never called Kuerig and had just returned the pot to the store. I cant tell you how many pods we havewasted. I just want coffee without grounds in it...we will see...it is being shipped.'),
(8575, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-16', 'great for us with multiple people in the family we use this every morning before work to fill travel mugs. both like a different favors, and I like to use my grounds. kids like it for the hot chocolate, and in the evening for tea before I got to bed.'),
(8576, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-16', 'Perfect for me I needed something for use only on weekends for a cup or two of coffee. This was easy to set up and operate. I don\'t waste coffee anymore. Love it!!!'),
(8577, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Absolutely Perfect!! We use this brewer every day for single cups or with the carafe. I love the fact of strength adjustment as well as cup sizes.'),
(8578, 13, 2, 2, '2016-03-19', 'Not hot enough! I was excited to purchase this as my very 1st Keurig machine and the price was not over my budget. I like the simplicity look of this machine but after a few use I find this machine fall short on a couple of performance issue. The water does not get hot enough! I have to sometimes fall back on my old school drip coffee maker on super cold mornings for a really hot cup. Also, I\'ve wasted quite a few new pods because the machine does not recognize it. Try taking the same pod out and putting it back or unplugging the machine to trick it and it still does the same thing. Not really happy for wasting a perfectly new pod.'),
(8579, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-27', 'Enjoying it so far! I tend to drink coffee a few days a week, haven\'t gotten to the everyday cup. This is perfect for me, when I want coffee or tea, I can brew a cup and go on without leftovers. I think it is quick to brew a cup and it comes out perfectly hot. I like that I can make the coffee stronger. It does take up a bit of counter space but I can get over that. And I hope they come up with a pod that you can put your own coffee in it instead of having to buy pods. But overall I am very satisfied with my brewer!'),
(8580, 13, 2, 2, '2016-03-19', 'Poor instructions makes me wonder... I like the looks of this item BUT the instructions are terrible! What is all this extra stuff in the carton? I see a five inch long cylindrical clear plastic thing that is not labeled and not referred to in the instructions, A \"Brewer Maintenance Accessory\" that the instructions use its Name (see above in quotes) more than the tell you WHY you need to use it, two extra filters (thanks, but there are no instructions on how to install the filters nor is there any indications that it comes preinstalled (or not). So I sit here and wonder, do I need to install one of these puppies, or do I have two spares?.. hmnm. Additonally, there like 3 or 4 sets of individual instructions between the maker itself and some of the accessories rather than all included in the main manual. Its like they spent the whole budget on a nice-looking coffee maker and then phoned in the important parts of the consumer experience. What a nice downer before I even make the first cup. I am not sure if I have it assembled correctly or if the important water filter is preinstalled. Of course, in response to this review I will get a canned \"Oh, I\'m sorry...\" response that nearly everyone else got.'),
(8581, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-20', 'Funny plastic taste I have used Keurig makers for many many years. The new 2.0 has a flaw - no matter what we brew - coffee, hot chocolate, tea even water tastes like burnt plastic.'),
(8582, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-19', 'Soo much better than expected! Debated buying this for a while and it was worth it! It\'s easy, convenient, and I have a nice variety of coffee to choose from. I also love that I can brew tea in it. It doesn\'t take up much space in my kitchen which is also a plus. Wish I would\'ve bought one sooner! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8583, 13, 2, 4, '2016-05-17', 'Obsessed with my Keurig! My basic K200 series was on sale this Christmas for only $10 more than the Mini was 4 years ago, which I\'d lost while moving. Couldn\'t resist the price. I bought the reusable K2 cup which adds functionality and size variations. I can use any coffee I want! It works perfectly, no waste, no mess! I love this thing!'),
(8584, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-07', 'K200 can\'t brew one cup of coffe I purchased the K200 to replace a true single cup Keurig. It worked great for a bout 5 months. Now I have to babysit it just to get one cup of coffee. It only gives you about 2 oz, of less each time. It takes about 4 to five times to get one cup, I tried just the hot water function and it seems to work fine. I tried cleaning it and it made only full cup and then went back to its old ways. I use it at work. We have an older Keurig at home that has worked great. My frustration level is on the rise and I almost feel like tossing the thing in the trash.'),
(8585, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Delicious I love this Keurig the coffee is hot and delicious my old keurig wouldn\'t heat coffee so it didn\'t taste brewed properly'),
(8586, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-11', 'I am very satisfied with my Keurig coffee maker.  It is easier to use than my one cup Keurig coffee  maker. I love how I can measure the proportions that I want and it has a coffee filter, for better tasting coffee.   I also like the new color choices, the color Oasis matches my kitchen beautifully.'),
(8587, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-19', 'Great Brewer I was excited when i received the Keurig 2.0. So i tested it out the same day I got it. I liked the many different settings and how quiet and easy it was to use.. The only dowwn side is if your brewering a larger cup. It gives you a weaker cup coffee. And, I\'m slightly dissapointed that the coffee pot was not included.'),
(8588, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-29', 'Great upgrades from the original! We purchased the original Keurig when it first came out, and used it for quite some time. Now we have this version, and are impressed with the upgrades and better features than the original model. Pros: Quiet-so much quieter than the first version. Lots more options when brewing. You can opt for a \"strong\" brew, change the amount of water used, or (my favorite) just heat water! Love that feature for brewing tea. This version has a carafe that you can fill with using special pods. I\'d love to try this out for brewing a large quantity, but it was not included with my package. This version is also smaller than the original. Love that saved counter space. I love that you can descale your machine. We had the original version of the Keurig and this was not something that was mentioned/recommended (if I remember right). Such a great way to keep your machine running great. Cons: The water chamber signals needing to be refilled when it still has 1/3 of the water left in it. At our house, my husband and I drink multiple cups of coffee each day, so it needs to be refilled frequently. The coffee is not equal to a strong cup you\'d get from an espresso machine (which is what we use to make coffee prior to getting this Keurig.) But, if you like coffee, don\'t need a crazy strong brew (even with the strong feature), this machine is quiet, easy to clean, and easy peasy to use. Such a great product (especially when comparing to the original one!).'),
(8589, 13, 2, 2, '2016-01-01', 'Environmentally Unfriendly - Received as a gift & returning Received as a gift & will return. Too much plastic waste and very environmentally unfriendly (can\'t imagine justifying all that plastic sitting in landfills from these machines). And, the cost is just ridiculous not to mention the maintenance. We use a few ceramic and glass Melitta style over the cup cones that work wonderfully for great tasting coffee with a cost of less than $20. They are easy and quick to clean and most importantly are environmentally friendly. Rather than using this machine at the present cost of the pods I would just go out to have coffee at Starbucks if I wanted to waste money.'),
(8590, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-22', 'K250 - Small in Size, Big on Features Love this coffee maker! It fits perfectly on the corner of my desk and is there when I need it most. The extra brew strength feature is great for those Monday mornings we all have. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8591, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Love it The price, color, design and not loud like the other  Keurigs I have owned'),
(8592, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', 'This product makes my mornings worth getting up for I use this coffee everyday I am a first time user. I love the variety and the fun in making the coffee. Everytime I use it I feel like I\'m on vacation. I am thrilled that I purchased this for myself as a gift It was a great ideaeyedot'),
(8593, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-23', 'Nice little machine I wish this one came with the carafe. If it has the capability, it should come with it. The water tank doesn\'t seem as sturdy as my old machine. Also because its on the back, its hard to reattach when its full, so I have resorted to using a pitcher to refill it without having to take it off.'),
(8594, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Love my new Keurig! I absolutely love my new Keurig! It is amazing! I use it for hot water for my tea as well as for my kids hot chocolate. Every morning while on the run I can quickly make a cup of coffee to take on my drive around to my kids schools and practices. I work from home and have short break times having this Keurig allows me to quickly make a cup of coffee and or tea without added stress. highly recommend this product!'),
(8595, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-13', 'Love this Keurig! Absolutely love this model! Bought it for the office and everyone finds it so easy to use. It\'s quick and quiet. I like that it has a water filter because not often at the office do you have filtered water! Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(8596, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-27', 'Great for Small Spaces! I love this product! It is great quality like the Keurig 2.0 but it\'s much more compact. I think its a huge step up from the Keurig Mini but just under the 2.0 because of the smaller water reservoir. If you live in a small area by yourself or with one other person this is the most ideal Keurig you could get! Everything you would want/need from a coffee maker!'),
(8597, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-04', 'Great Looking Product Hoping it will last longer than our previous Keurig as the last one only held up for a few months.'),
(8598, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-01', 'Oh heck Am upset that Pacific Chai cups will not work in this model. Our old Kuerig gave up the ghost and now this unit just does not cut the mustard. Sorry I bought it.'),
(8599, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Love the exclusive Target color! This was such a hit with the family Christmas morning. Everyone got something they loved from hot chocolate to flavored coffees. Easy for me.  The aqua color is such a hit, I\'m going to need to Order more for gifts. This one gets you about 3-4 cups before having to refill.'),
(8600, 13, 2, 3, '2016-03-25', 'Only have two complaints for my Keurig I love the color of my Keurig (Off White)... It heats up pretty fast & thats about it. However I do NOT like that you have to replace the filter on the inside so soon after purchasing, and also don\'t like that I had to buy reusable k-cups to put coffee grinds into if it doesnt recognize the brand im using.'),
(8601, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-09', 'Great Product This is our second Keurig and it is just such a great product! I love having pods for coffee because my husband drinks regular and I drink decaf. The coffee comes out fast and does not take long to heat up. We got the sandy pearl color and it is very pretty and looks crisp and clean on the counter. I would definitely recommend this product.'),
(8602, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Great coffee maker! I had an old keurig that I didn\'t like since you couldn\'t choose different amounts it made. I love that you have the options of making a whole pot of coffee if you want! It\'s very stylish in the kitchen and easy to use.'),
(8603, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-13', 'Perfect solution for my busy mornings! This guy literally takes 15 seconds to brew. You just pop a k-cup into the machine, select one of the brew buttons, and you\'re done. No having to clean out coffee grinders, no having to wait, no having to deal with espresso nonsense. Pop the used k-cup out and you\'re done. No fuss, no muss. And even though we try to steer clear of appliances that take up counter space because toaster + blender + coffee maker + bean grinder + crockpot = no counter space, this model was so much more narrow than our coffee maker and fit perfectly!'),
(8604, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Love it The sandy pearl looks so pretty in my kitchen. Love it.'),
(8605, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-28', 'This model has awesome upgrades/features! We bought the original Keurig right after they came out and used it for quite some time. We have the 2.0, and love all of the new features! Pros: Quiet-so much quieter than the first version. Lots more options when brewing. You can opt for a \"strong\" brew, change the amount of water used, or (my favorite) just heat water! Love that feature for brewing tea. This version has a carafe that you can fill with using special pods. I\'d love to try this out for brewing a large quantity of coffee, but it was not included with my package. I love that you can descale your machine. We had the original version of the Keurig and this was not something that was mentioned/recommended (if I remember right). Such a great way to keep your machine running great. Cons: The water chamber signals needing to be refilled when it still has 1/3 of the water left in it. At our house, my husband and I drink multiple cups of coffee each day, so it needs to be refilled frequently. The coffee is not equal to a strong cup you\'d get from an espresso machine (which is what we used to make coffee prior to getting this Keurig.) But, if you like coffee, don\'t need a crazy strong brew (even using the strong feature), this machine is quiet, easy to clean, and easy peasy to use. Such a great product (especially when comparing to the original one!).'),
(8606, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-01', 'a wolf in sheep\'s clothing LOVED the color, and got a great deal. Got it set up, and discovered that it will NOT use any off-brand K-cups, only Keurig-approved/branded ones. In addition, there is no way to use the adapters for bag coffee. It is also a bit unstable - it rocks back when you lift up the handle. I am extremely disappointed in this product, and will be returning it for a refund as soon as possible.'),
(8607, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Great purchase I love it! So easy to use and it\'s a great size so fits anywhere'),
(8608, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-26', 'New Keurig 2.0 how to use product and what\'s good about it. Negative stuff helpful too especially before purchase. Features are important.'),
(8609, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-03', 'Keurig 2.0 I bought the 2.0 in Jan 2016 and it only worked 1 month without problems. Since then I have gone through all of the processes that are suggested in the manual and on the website, three times. I will not work for 2-3 days and then just start working again. I have used a Keurig brewer for several years, at home and work, but wish I had not bought the 2.0.'),
(8610, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-17', 'I love my Keurig 2.0 I am just not up to waiting for my decaf and now three minutes it is in my cup. Love the taste with the Vanilla. Could write a book on how happy I am with it. If anyone finds fault with-it I don\'t know why. Not one con with me. My Daughter and entire family have one and if I knew how wonderful it was, would have gotten one sooner.'),
(8611, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-30', 'My favorite new kitchen gadget! I never thought I\'d get a Keurig until my boyfriend\'s parents got one at Christmas. Since then, I\'ve been wanting one so badly! Target had a great deal on the new 2.0 model, so I caved. I got it in my favorite color, and the turquoise is gorgeous. Easy to use and clean. My favorite feature is the touch screen. Though I haven\'t used it yet, I like that you can use the bigger K-mug pods with this model also. I\'ve been enjoying my coffee iced with milk every morning since I got it. This is probably my best purchase this summer! Keurig even has great deals on pods once you register with their website, including free pod boxes. I\'ve already received 2 free boxes with the purchase of 2, and they offer more with a product review. So thanks, Keurig, for the awesome product and for the free pods for this review!'),
(8612, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'It\'s terrific! We love it! It\'s pretty, functional, easy to use & fun!'),
(8613, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-14', 'Must buy! Overall this is a really great machine! I\'ve never had a Keurig before so I was pleasantly surprised when I started using this specific machine. It\'s great for a quick cup of coffee but a bit difficult if you don\'t like the flavors or specific brands since only cups can be used. But I really enjoy the machine overall! Super easy to use.'),
(8614, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-30', 'works fine..... Best use is making coffee first thing in the morning when you don\'t want to wake anyone else. The \'strength control\' also works well.'),
(8615, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Obsessed! For the amount of coffee my household consumes, I can\'t believe we didn\'t upgrade sooner. We are a Keurig house, and had a K45 for the past few years. It was awesome_then we got this guy, and boy are we in love. It looks so sleek on our counter, and technology challenged husband even can use the touchscreen with ease! The carafe is amazing and It makes life so much more convienent when we want to drink more than one cup at a time. I think if it wasn\'t apparent before, this coffee maker seals the deal for us being loyal to Keurig!'),
(8616, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'Kids love it Interesting thing is that we aren\'t coffee drinkers but it\'s nice we can make hot chocolate or brew cider with it.  My kids use it every day.  The only concern is that it won\'t let you use any k cups that aren\'t approved by keurig.  You can google keurig hacks to use off brand cups which work but it is a pain to have to do that.'),
(8617, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-16', 'I LOVE this Brewer!!! I love this brewer! I received it free from Influenster for testing purposes and i couldn\'t have gotten a product that fits me more to test! I like the versatility of the cup/mug/carafe sizes and i can make my hot tea and my daughters cocoa with it also! LOVE! **I will be receiving complemenatary kcups to review this item**'),
(8618, 13, 2, 1, '2016-08-16', 'Disappointment I bought my brewer about 2 months ago.   I have been very happy with my previous 3 keurig Brewers.   Unfortunately this brewer has not lived up to my expectations.   It is small which is nice, but there is no auto turn off feature, you cannot pre-set the brew size, and the reservoir is small and in an awkward place.   I just now had a needle maintenance error, and although it is not on the FAQs for the brewer, it was on multiple other sites and seems like a common problem because there is a needle maintenance tool included with the brewer (who knew?).   I would not recommend this model at all.'),
(8619, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Keurig I absolutely love mine!'),
(8620, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-14', 'We (my hubby & I) were impressed with the solid feel and easy to use.  Only our 2nd keurig & this is better in every way.  We aren\'t \"techy\", but touch screen is easy to use.  Haven\'t used the included \"tool\" for easy clean when machine tells me it needs it as of yet, but like the concept.  May try the k-mug size k cups sometime in the future  since mug size option was another thing helped decide on this model.'),
(8621, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-17', 'Poor waterhandling design Having owned a Tassimo brewer I find the design very disappointing. It takes up more counter space, the water compartment is small and awkward to handle plus you cannot empty the internal water compartment for storage or moving. Unfortunately Tassimo seems to be going the way of Betamax.'),
(8622, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-27', 'Great Gave as a gift and they love it'),
(8623, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-30', 'a treat to have in my house I love Keriug 2.O K200 brewing system. The set up was simple and easy and it so easy to use to make myself a quick cup of coffee or beverage that I want! I use to make hot chocolate coffee or even Snapple iced tea. I like that when you have company that u can make individual cups of coffee or other drinks without having to brew a whole pot. I highly recommend this product'),
(8624, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-10', 'Perfect I\'ve been looking into buying a Keurig for a while now. I would always use the one my Aunt has whenever I went over her house. I like this model because it\'s simple and affordable. It\'s very convenient for me, especially when I\'m in a hurry before I go to class. I like that I can just make one cup for myself and not waste a whole pot of coffee anymore.'),
(8625, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-06', 'Best Coffee Maker !! I have just purchased this particular brewer - Keurig K250 Coffee Maker. Not only am I familiar with the \'Keurig\', but you could not deal with a more caring, honest Company!! They will answer any and all questions, and their Associates are helpful and cheerful!!!'),
(8626, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-19', 'Awesome Keurig I use my keurig every morning and it makes my day go much better. There are a lot of kcups just doing some experimenting to find the ones I like the most.'),
(8627, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-18', 'LOVE LOVE LOVE my Keurig !! I received my Keurig Elite 2 yrs ago as a gift. I use it pretty much daily all year long as it is so fast and handy to use. I still have my other coffee maker when needed for guests / full pot of coffee, but I love this Keurig. I agree with others about how costly the k-cups can be if not purchased on sale, but I get mine from amazon at a much cheaper rate and they all fit this Keurig with no problems! I would recommend it to others all day long !'),
(8628, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-14', 'i love this product! I just recently use my Keurig 2.0 Brewer and i gotta say, i love it! it\'s really easy to set up and easy to use. If you love coffee, you will love coffee even more by buying this product! i like how the brewer does all the work and knows how much water and coffee you need in different sizes of cups. I recommend you to buy this product, you won\'t regret it!'),
(8629, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-25', 'Not what I expected.... I use this replacement product for home use daily. Used for tea and coffee. I loved the 1st one I bought, it lasted 15 months. the new one had problems within the 1st month...the replacement I was sent has had problems with plugging since day one. I believe it was refurbished and not brand new. It also has a weak spring that doesn\'t hold the lid up so I can put the k-cup in....disappointed and disillusioned after such a good experience with my 1st product in 2014....'),
(8630, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-17', 'Best Coffee Machine My classmates and I use the Keurig 2.2 everyday before class starts. Its easy, simple and convenient. Everybody can use their different K-Cups and different flavors. Cleaning it is a breeze.'),
(8631, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-11', 'Great product!! Great coffee making!!! So easy to use!!! Perfect coffee everytime.'),
(8632, 13, 2, 3, '2015-09-26', 'Replacement Brewer for the K250 which is now called the K200 After 4 tries I finally received a brewer that works. Originally it was called the K250 and they changed the name to the K200. Due to the change they no longer give you the free coffee samples which is fine. It took them 4 months to finally get me the correct water filter kit. With this order I received a water filter but they left out the 2 free cartridges and they left out the descaling solution. As far as I\'m concerned when you replace something it should be the entire kit as advertised. Also when I registered this brewer I was told I would receive another email with a coupon good for 2 boxes of coffee when you purchase 2 boxes with free shipping which they didn\'tdo. The first brewer didn\'t have the water filter kit and it took them 4 months to get one by them sending me a second brewer replacement kit. This second one was missing the drp tray so I had to keep the original from the first brewer. The 2nd brewer also had a crack in the plastic resorvior so I had to keep the one that came with the first brewer. So then they sent me a third brwer but they were out of the black and I wasn\'t told that was just temporary so I had to pick another color which was hidious if you\'re a guy. 2 days later when I wrote the review I received a call saying they could send the black one and this one works but my opinion is whether it\'s a replacement or not, everything that is supposed to come with the K250(K200) should still come with it. Last of all when I registered this brewer I was told specifically by the representative I would receive a coupon good for 2 free boxes of coffee when you purchase 2 by email even though it was a replacement. This did not happen at all. If you\'re going to purchase a brewer by Keurig don\'t believe everything they tell or promise you.'),
(8633, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-06', 'great product but........ I recently purchased the Keurig 2.0 K250. So had it a couple of day now. So far love the product some of the sample k-cups are good some are stale. just tried to contact customer support to find out about a reusable coffee filter for my model, but apparently one does not exist. I like the brewing system, however, customer support informed me that the new models have been out about a year now and still no reusable filter. I happened to ask when one might be available support said \"Maybe by Christmas.\" I find this to be frustrating. I love coffee and love to get my fresh roasted coffee directly from the roaster. But now I have to deal with \"possibly fresh\" K-pods?'),
(8634, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-18', 'My First Keurig I previously had a Tassimo, and the coffee was never hot enough. Bed Bath & Beyond was having a special offer and I had a gift card so decided to try the Keurig. Taste of coffee is much better and definitely hotter. I am happy with my decision except that I chose the K250 with 40 ounce water reservoir and although I am not a big coffee drinker, I find I need to refill the reservoir very often. That is disappointing and annoying, but I guess I should have taken the time to figure out that I should have purchased a model with a bigger reservoir.'),
(8635, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-24', 'I love it! I have this Keurig model and I really love it. It\'s troublefree, and it makes it so easy to fix a great cup of coffee. I especially like that it came with a water filter (I filter my drinking water) that fits down inside the water chamber. The only issue I have is sometimes it is difficult to get the unit to turn off - the touch screen is a bit tricky. But that\'s not a real problem. I would definitely recommend this one - it\'s easy to use and makes great coffee. (Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review).'),
(8636, 14, 2, 1, '2015-01-22', 'Most disappointing experience this week I bought this to make smoothies, something that is specifically shown on the box. I put in some ice cream, strawberries, and ice. The motor whirred and nothing moved and nothing was blended. Pushing fruit towards the base with a blending aid only caused the motor to start to burn out. This cannot crush ice or blend smoothies. Aside from the poor blending, the base was very unstable and wobbly. Even the assembly details on this page are incorrect, it does not come assembled.'),
(8637, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-10', 'Great fit the price Easy to use and clean.'),
(8638, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-06', 'Tried the Cuisinart line, and it didn\'t work. I use this product in my bedroom, since I don\'t want to wake my mom up in the middle of the night when I need coffee. This will be perfect for studying, since I can\'t stand sour coffee and thus can\'t bring a pot of coffee up with me. I got mine at Target for $80 something, although it did not come with pods. I\'d rather pick my own pods though, so this didn\'t bother me.'),
(8639, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-11', 'Poor Product I bought this product because it was on sale and I am on a tight budget and always wanted one. I bought it 3 days ago and it has only worked correctly for one day. I takes forever for it to heat and I have coffee grounds in my cup. I am always getting errors saying oops not a valid cup, which in fact it is. I am very said to say that I wasted my hard earned money on this product for a cup of coffee grounds. So if you are looking for a Kureg do buy this model. I am going to back to using my Mr. Coffee.'),
(8640, 14, 2, 4, '2015-12-08', 'Good value for the price It serves it\'s job and it was a good price!'),
(8641, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Love Love Love Love this product, I\'m the only coffee drinker in my house so it fits my needs perfectly! Best one I\'ve bought so far!'),
(8642, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-13', 'Very Happy With Our K250 We are enjoying our Keurig Coffee maker. We use it every day and have had 0 problems. It is quick and convenient, and quite stylish. We just wish mug pods were more available. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8643, 13, 2, 5, '2016-11-12', 'Love it for the color. Keep it for the ease of use. Works well with the carafe, as well as the optional cups from other manufacturers to load your own coffee in.'),
(8644, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-09', 'The \"strong\" option is a huge plus. We are not big fans of bitter/strong coffee, but sometimes my wife feels like having coffee with milk, in which case, she wants the coffee to be relatively strong. She says the \"strong\" setting is perfect for that purpose. Our previous brewer (K45, now in my office at work) didn\'t have this option, so she is very happy about it. I also sometimes want strong black coffee, so it works well for me, too. Another thing we really like about this product is the design of the water reservoir. In particular, the fact that it is transparent makes the whole brewer look much smaller than it actually is. We really think it is stylish and well-designed. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8645, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Love this brewer! Love this brewer! I love that there are more options in cup sizes. I also love the touch screen. It was difficult to find the color I wanted without ordering it, but I\'m so glad I waited and ordered it. This is definitely a step up from our old Keurig. My old pods do not work in this machine and I was a bit disappointed that there were no sample pods in the box so that I could at least try it when I got it set up. Love it though! Thanks Keurig for the free pods upon review.'),
(8646, 14, 2, 5, '2015-04-25', 'Best Blender I\'ve Owned It blends smoothies with ice in seconds!!!'),
(8647, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', '2nd Keurig 2.0 brweing system purchased. This purchase was of the K200 series. We wanted the zest orange but since that was out of stock we went with the purple brewer. We really like the large easy to fill water reservoir along with included easy install filter. Many different brew size options along with a strong option. This unit came with a upper pin cleaner that makes cleaning the system a lot easier than our older model. Lower portion of brewer lifts out for easy cleaning. Unit has easy to understand and program panel. Our brewer appears to be well built and should last quite awhile with little maintenance as our old system has. Brewed our first 2 cups and thought the temperature and strength of the coffee was very good. One thing we noticed is how quiet it is compared with our older brewer. My wife is thinking of swapping out the 2 and making this our primary system. Yes, Keurig is sending me a couple boxes of pods for this review. But that does not mater. If you open our cupboard above the brewer you will find around 50 boxes of pods. Everytime we think we have settled on one coffee we try another and then find we like that one also. Our company that comes to see us loves the large selection of coffees and teas that we have on hand. In summary, you cannot go wrong buying this or any of the 2.0 brewing systems. We have tried multiple brewers in the past and none compare to this.'),
(8648, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Great Coffee Maker K-250 We enjoy good coffee and start our day together having a morning cup before work. We talked about getting a Keurig and finally made the decision to purchase the K200 Series, K250. We absolutely love it and the variety of K-cup options available to us. It is so easy to use and looks wonderful on the counter. No mess, no more counting the scoops of coffee  it is really simple to use. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I received compensation / free product for my unbiased review.'),
(8649, 14, 2, 5, '2015-12-09', 'Worth for the Money Works as expected. Definitely recommend'),
(8650, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-22', 'Great new brewer This product is awesome! I recently got it and its made my mornings a lot easier. At the same time I\'m not spending a lot of money at my local coffee shop.'),
(8651, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-29', 'this is great for coffee This is my first and only coffee review :)'),
(8652, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-30', 'Must have! The Keurig K250 is one of the best brewers that I have ever used. The sleek and incognito design allows for the brewer to blend into a kitchen environment as well as fit in various location and positions. The touch screen display is simple and very appropriate for the device. The K250 never fails to brew my coffee in the morning and with every use, I get more and more hooked into the Keurig lifestyle. Who needs fancy drinks from overpriced coffee shops when you have a wide variety of K cups and new 2.0 K cups which allow you to brew up to a full Keurig pot or in my instance, a 14 oz cup every morning. Overall, I am very happy with my device and will continue to explore the wide range of K cups available to me. The sleekness and simple interface allow you to brew you coffee every morning at your own pace and still spares time to brew that second cup if needed.'),
(8653, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-07', 'Great too have Great too have recommend too anyone that love coffee'),
(8654, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Love it! Love it! The only reason we didn\'t get a Keurig before it was the fact that you could do 1 cup at the time, love this 2.0 version. It is really quiet and fast. You have to make sure to buy the pods that say Keurig on the box if not it will not work!! It won\'t fit my husband travel mug but if you take the base off you are all set ! I had made tea and it tasted fine, which I was concerned about, but I don\'t know if the more we use it with coffe this will change or not. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review\"'),
(8655, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-26', 'Good machine for the price! \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\" Use this product on daily basis, usually several times daily. Several cup sizes and love the machine so far! It\'s easy to use and easy to clean. The only issue that I have seen is that frequently it has stopped brewing to goes to the pre-heating cycle. I have called customer service at Keurig and they were very helpful. They went through some troubleshooting steps and informed me if it continued to call back. Glad that I made this purchase!'),
(8656, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'simply love it! I was disappointed that I could only use Keurig brand k-cups at first. Other than that, I really enjoy it!'),
(8657, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Awesome brewing system Very easy and quick system to use! Love it!'),
(8658, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-20', 'so far so good I love have several flavors to choose from at any time a day and not having to brew an entire pot.'),
(8659, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-23', 'Love my new Keurig 2.0 !! Use this product on a daily basis. Love the touch screen which guides your every move. Appreciate the option of brewing a Carafe or a single cup. The biggest problem you will have with the Keurig 2.0 is deciding on the color ! All so beautiful and stylish. Thank you Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(8660, 13, 2, 3, '2015-11-09', 'I am having issues already and just got it last week. When I go to brew a cup of coffee...it will start brewing but then an error message states that I may need to call maintenance phone number. Not sure what that means but the pods brew and then there are grounds in my coffee also.'),
(8661, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-01', 'Great features, great color, efficient brewer I have had several Keurig brewers and they surpass any competitor'),
(8662, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-11', 'Quick and Easy It is always heating the water. I wonder about electric usage. It makes a quick cup of coffee. Its a pro and a con. Be careful buying pods at the store. If they are not Keurig pods the machine will not brew it. Love I can choose strong brew or ounces of water. Can have it dispense water to rinse it out after hot chocolate.'),
(8663, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Awesome Great price, Easy pick up in store. Thank you Target :)'),
(8664, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-24', 'Worst Keurig Ever The system offers the ability to brew a 4, 6, 8, or 10 ounce cup. If choose 10 ounce and the majority of the time get 4 ounces. I choose 4 ounces and get anywhere from 2 to 10 ounces all at once. The computer system does not distribute the water measurements correctly and has caused much frustration. I will never buy a Keurig again!'),
(8665, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-08', 'Bad Model Love the keurigs. This model is one of the worst models I have ever use. The reuseable pods are only accepted 1 time out of 3 this is totally unacceptable; can\'t even give it away this machine needs to be updated or fixed'),
(8666, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-29', 'Doesn\'t Brew Correct Size Got this for the hubby to replace our older Keurig, it is horrible, he wants to go back to the older one. Can only make a small cup of hot water and can\'t brew a travel size mug without doing it twice. You press ten ounces but it doesn\'t brew and come out to ten, if you do ten oz and 4oz then it comes out a little less than the travel mug....we can\'t be doing things twice. Super disappointed!'),
(8667, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-27', 'nice machine I just received this a week ago and have used it everyday since it arrived. It is very convenient to use and takes less time than brewing in a traditional machine. I think it would make a great addition to my office and am considering purchasing another.'),
(8668, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-10', 'My favorite thing to wake up too I wake up super early every day so having this product is perfect. Love Keurig items and i love this new machine. I hate cleaning it but everything else makes up for it.'),
(8669, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-10', 'Very happy When I called customer service complaining about the K250 brewer making a weird noise they immediately mailed out a new turquoise keurig brewer. Also, when I bought some K-pods that did not have the keurig seal the customer service lady immediately mailed out two free boxes of pods. Everything works great, and the customer service team was professional, and took the time to resolve the real problem.'),
(8670, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Awesome price Got it on sale for 79.00 when my dad asked my three days before Xmas to go buy my mom one  for him ... works great and didn\'t have any problem using community coffee know cups.... I even went buy the model above this one for myself and didn\'t have problems with the other brand of kcups..... didn\'t splatter coffee like my kitchen cuisine  I had before.'),
(8671, 13, 2, 4, '2016-05-30', 'This is the coffee-maker for me. Single serve saves time . This is great in the pm when one/two cups is all you need! Saves time & money! Would like a larger brewer if you need more cups for guests, 4 cups would be great!'),
(8672, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-11', 'Smaller Size but still great coffee maker Use my machine on a daily basis an love it. I have limited counter space so this size works best for me but still offers me options in sizes for my coffee, which I love.'),
(8673, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-17', 'Simple and Convenient It\'s extremely easy to use and has all of the features that my wife and I need! It can brew 9 different sizes with the capabilities of using the Carafe sizes if we were wanting larger \'pots.\' For the price, you simply can\'t beat the convenience and the simplicity of this Keurig. I\'m sure it will have a permanent location on our kitchen counter top!  Additionally, Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8674, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Statement piece I simply wanted to upgrade from K50 and liked the different color options with this one. The only down side so far is the water bin is smaller and I feel it takes a bit longer to warm up and brew. Otherwise I enjoy having it! Also caught a great deal right before Christmas'),
(8675, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-12', '\"Coffee Brigade\" Our company has the word \"Friends\" as part of its corporate name. We are extremely delighted to have Keurig join our circle of \"Friends\" and welcome it into our small business culture. It is a treat to have such a selection of coffee \"flavor friends\" and everyone truly enjoys it. All of our employees were elated when we bought the new Keurig after we moved into our new location. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8676, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-09', 'The 2.0 Is much better than the mini brewer! I had the mini brewer, but keurig hooked me up with a replacement so I got the 2.0 k250 in turquoise. So far I love it, makes good coffee, easy to use. Much nicer than the mini-brewer I replaced. they are like worlds apart. It came with lots of accessories. Perfect for those quick cups before work. And we love the color so much that we decided to add more turquoise accents to our kitchen. I can only hope it is more durable than the last two keurig brewers I had. But the technology seems so much better, I haven\'t found anything I don\'t like about it yet. Hopefully recycling will come soon. Thanks, Keurig, for the free products for this review but even with free products I am honest in my opinion.'),
(8677, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-29', 'Pleased with my purchase The Keurig K250 is the first Keurig brewer I have owned. Overall, I am very pleased with this purchase! I find it works great for everyday use in my home. I love that the new 2.0 models have the ability to brew a carafe, although I found it strange that this brewer does not come with a carafe. I also love the strong brew setting, and I have found a reusable filter so I can still use my own coffee grounds in this brewer. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8678, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Mega Coffee-Drinker I have always been skeptical about Keurigs, but my partner and I agreed to get this instead of a Coffee Pot/Hot Water brewer. I am in love. I got the re-usable K-cup to go with it and it actually brews my individual cups really well. They aren\'t burnt or weak.  I am now a believer. Plus, my partner, who can\'t drink coffee, can have tea whenever he wants to.'),
(8679, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-10', 'Easy to use, upset about the pods I have loved keurig for years now. I recently saw the 2.0 in the store and bought it for my office. However, the downside that I have is that I have many pods that Kuerig does not have that it will not let me use. I wish that there would have been some sort of disclaimer on it because that would have possibly changed my mind about buying it. Also, I have been having an issue with a small amount coffee grounds ending up in my cup when it brews. I have used the maintenance tool multiple times and it has not alleviated it.'),
(8680, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-22', 'weak brew, not happy with this product. I want my old Keurig back. It\'s obvious this is Keurig\'s silly attempt to keep us from using our own grind of coffee and to force us to spend almost $1/pod for others. I have had 4 previous Keurig makers and cannot recommend this one to anyone. Back to my French press--more fun anyway.'),
(8681, 13, 2, 2, '2015-10-03', 'Constantly Malfunctioning This is a product in which I enjoyed for nearly a full month. Then, it became a nightmare. My machine started getting clogged every week forcing me to get q-tips and spend 15 minutes working to fix the problem. I do not know if this is a problem others are having but I find it extremely inconvenient that I have to put so much work into something that cost me over $100. I will be returning this item and buying a different model hoping that I do not encounter the same situation or Keurig will have lost a life long customer.'),
(8682, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Love it Love it! Wasn\'t sure I would, but it is great.'),
(8683, 14, 2, 4, '2015-09-14', 'very good very good makes less noise and very good for day to day functions'),
(8684, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-23', 'Makes great coffee This brewer makes makes great coffee. So far I\'ve only used it for coffee, but I\'ll try other drinks soon. I have no problem finding k-cup pods in local stores, but carafe packs are harder to find localy. There are plenty of on-line stores who sell k-cup and carafe packs, however. It is quick and easy to operate, however it took me a while to figure out how to turn it off. It did not power off automaticaly. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8685, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-17', 'Little space, lots of coffee! I have had an older version of the Keurig for a long time and it was a lot noisier than this one. I also love how small and compact the 2.0 K250 model is. It fits nicely on my countertop without taking up too much room. It is easy to refill the water and clean and makes delicious coffee! My favorite part about it is that I am able to brew a small cup of coffee for myself or use my new Keurig carafe to brew a batch for a whole group! Highly recommend upgrading to this version its fantastic!'),
(8686, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-20', 'Best Keurig Yet This, in my opinion, is the best product that Keurig has come out with to date for simple coffee. It is small, fast and makes a great cup of coffee, tea, hot chocolate, etc. I would definitely recommend this anyone.'),
(8687, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-09', 'Sorry I waited so long I\'m what many would call a coffee snob. However, I officially call myself an enthusiast. I roast my own green coffee beans, have a $500 grinder and a $2000 espresso machine. To most I\'m the snob but trust me, the snobs have $900 grinders and $6000 machines. Anyway, my wife never messes with my stuff and only occasionally asks for a decaf mocha latte. Decaf is a hassle as I\'m not set up for it so she\'s always wanted a Keurig after hearing our friends talk about them. We finally bought a 250 and it\'s great! I love the convenience and I\'m surprised at how good everything tastes. I always thought these things just pumped hot water through some instant coffee powder but no way. This is good stuff. Don\'t let the following disclaimer fool you. If I didn\'t like it, I\'d say so! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8688, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-21', 'its AWESOME I love the new color, also i love that its compact, and the touch screen too. its just nice to have a coffee right away specially in the morning where you can\'t function correctly yet until you are done with your coffee.'),
(8689, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-28', 'Great Model, Great Price After upgrading from my Keurig Mini Brewer and having this model for a little over a week now, I have to say that I have yet to be disappointed. I use my new Keurig everyday. I love the fact that I can brew various size beverages with the touch of a button. I like to emphasize that it\'s a button because my last model had no buttons; you just filled the reservoir appropriately. The sleek new design is also a huge plus. I have a black model and it makes a great addition to my modern looking kitchen. The fact that the water reservoir can hold a decent amount of water is another plus. I live with a few other roommates (I just graduated from college) and they all use it also. We don\'t have to worry about filling it after or before each use. I think this model is great for everyone. Even if I was living in a dorm, I\'d bring it with me. As it stands, it looks great in my medium sized kitchen.'),
(8690, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-05', 'Love this handy machine! I love the flexibility of use that it has for all different sized cups & mugs and even a carafe! I got the red to go with my kitchen so that was a plus.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8691, 13, 2, 4, '2015-11-06', 'Another great machine with a few cons. I have owned MANY Keurig machines. The VUE being my favorite and I am so bummed I can\'t get that one anymore. I loved being able to get an orange machine this time but I am going to miss the auto on/off feature and having a clock. I love the smaller compact size though so will overlook the cons. I have only had this one day but I am sure it will work just as nicely as my other machines.'),
(8692, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-26', 'best purchase of 2015 I could not say enough good things about this Keurig 2.0. It\'s absolutely amazing and has made my morning routine so much easier. This Keurig is so sleek and incredibly efficient. The touch screen is so easy to use and I love the brewing strength and cup size options. My coffee is ready in seconds and I\'m already out the door. I love the variety of K-cups this Keurig can brew (over 500), and how many options this gives me everyday. I\'m extremely satisfied with my purchase and would highly recommend it to anyone.'),
(8693, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-26', 'Keurig 2.0 We received this as a Christmas present, but, upon reading to owner\'s manual, we have come to the conclusion that it will not be cost effective for us. Too much maintenance plus money after money. Special descaling solution -$13.00, Carafe -$20.00, reusable K-Pod - 1 for $15.00, the very high cost of K-Pods & the filter -$15.00 every 2 months!! We are retired & on a fixed income. There is no way we can afford this. The machine WILL be returned, unless there are other possibilities. It\'s a VERY good idea but it\'s a gift that NEVER stops costing. We will stick with our 2 year old Wolfgang Puck coffee maker. To clean all we need is vinegar!!'),
(8694, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-24', 'Nice Upgrade for Keurig I decided to purchase the new Keurig to supplement my Dolce Gusto which is perfect for \"fancy\" drinks but not so much coffee. I loved the new compact size and color options, which works for my small apartment. A few things I would like to change is the option for non-keurig branded k-cups and a better iced coffee option. When it brews hot it always melts the ice which is not very pleasant. Over all though, great machiene. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8695, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-29', 'Keurig 200 I live this model. It was easy to put together and it makes the best coffee! It even prepares the coffee quickly and is very efficient! Highly recommended!'),
(8696, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Love my new Keurig! I love how easy it is to use the Keurig 2.0. The digital screen provides all of your choices. It\'s great that there is an option for a \"strong\" cup, even at the 10oz size. That is such an awesome improvement. Overall, I love how Keurig has made my morning coffee simple!'),
(8697, 13, 2, 3, '2016-04-23', 'Not as good as the first generation Love Keurigs but....this one came with a container so you could use regular coffee... Never works. Keurig should have left the water container on the side, to hard to refill in back. Only gives you a 6 oz or 4 oz option when making tea. I liked the old 10 oz option. This one was a disappointment compared to the older one in my vacation home.'),
(8698, 14, 2, 1, '2014-07-29', 'Complete garbage Tried to crush up ice cubes - didn\'t do much at all. Waste of money.'),
(8699, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Modern, sleek design This is my third Keurig and I love this new smaller, sleeker design.'),
(8700, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Perfect cup of coffee I think this is a great product. I love how there are so many k-cup brands and flavors so you can have a different cup of coffee every time. It is a bit noisy using it compared to other machines I have used but it isn\'t a big problem. I also feel like the water goes pretty fast, but maybe the tank is smaller than other ones I have tried. Overall this is a great product and I would recommend to anyone.'),
(8701, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-12', 'Great Product I love receiving the K200. It is very convenient. I can start the coffee and while its preheating I can finish my last steps of walking out of the door. I love that ever cup taste refreshing. And my house smells great.'),
(8702, 13, 2, 3, '2015-06-29', '7 out of 10. Had expected better! This is my first personal keurig brewer. Have been using keurig in office, travel so thought of picking for home. Surprisingly this is not at all what I expected. It does not heat up the coffee as the older versions, and makes out a splattering sound at the end.'),
(8703, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-19', 'Great upgrade I\'ve been using a Mr. Coffee Single Serve for years, so it was time for an upgrade. This machine looks sleek and stylish on my countertop, and the display makes it easy to use. Also, the option of brewing a stronger cup is definitely a plus for me. All in all a great upgrade. I have to admit though, that the amount of time it took to preheat was a bit longer than I expected, but it brews cup after cup pretty quickly right after. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8704, 13, 2, 3, '2015-05-01', 'It is okay I have an older Keurig but thought I would give this one a try. I do like how it was smaller but when I want to have hot water for my tea the highest oz that I can have is 6oz. I personally like 8oz. Also I do not like that I can not use any kcup/reusable cup. I try to be environmentally conscious and using a kcup every day is not. I would recommend just using a french press. You will get much better coffer for a lot cheaper.'),
(8705, 13, 2, 1, '2016-09-27', 'Waste of money This is a terrible appliance. I bought this to replace my old Keurig, which I loved, and I could not be more disappointed. I bought and returned two that were nonfunctional until finally receiving a third machine that worked. I have used this for a year, in my home, with one roommate and it no longer works. I will not be buying another Keurig. Even when it was working, the taste of the coffee is average at best, no matter what coffee we used or how filtered the water was.'),
(8706, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-06', 'Awesome purchase! Best coffee machine that I have ever purchased. Easy to use. I love the touch screen feature.'),
(8707, 14, 2, 3, '2014-12-07', 'personal blender jar Does it include personal blender jar? I thought it includes and in Instruction Manual, there is some images. but it is for three models. That\'s why I could not be sure. for now, it works not bad. But it is a little bit noisy.'),
(8708, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-04', 'Any Keurig I love the Keurig but it only lasts a year before I have to buy a new one. I\'m on my 4h one.'),
(8709, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-05', 'perfect! We love it!'),
(8710, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-22', 'They\'ve done it again! I love my Keurig. I drink coffee everyday and this prevents me from going out and buying coffee at a coffee shop. I like the speed, the small size, that I can make a pot of company is over. I wish I could easily fit taller cups without losing the drip tray.'),
(8711, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-16', 'Awesome Coffee I have used my new Keurig several times a day. I\'m drinking more coffee than I ever had before. The flavor is exceptional. Wish I had bought one a few years ago when they first came out.'),
(8712, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-16', 'Great I do really love this coffee pot, I love the look of it. I love the digital screen. I love the difference size options. It\'s quick, quiet and convenient. The only thing I do not like about this product is not being able to use refillable k-cups. Although the pods that come with it are fantastic, I am a coffee addict. I have 5 different pounds in my cupboard that I can\'t use with this pot. I like that the instructions give you information on recycling the cups, but it is not as environmentally friendly as it sounds.'),
(8713, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-18', 'Good product and great costumer service I\'m totally satisfied with keurig.the product is good and costumer service is the best.'),
(8714, 13, 2, 3, '2016-01-08', 'Fun to use We had trouble with the registered item -- it kept cycling back to the preheat and we had trouble seating the K cup. We called customer service and they replaced the entire unit -- the new one works great and we have enjoyed the convenience of brewing one cup of our choosing at a time.'),
(8715, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-31', 'Worth the money- great upgrade As a Keurig mini owner, I upgraded to the k250 and it is way better. The water reservoir is removable and easy to clean which was a previous issue with the Keurig Mini because the water reservoir for the Mini is non-removable. This makes it hard to clean especially with mineralization. Since I am an everyday coffee drinker and am now addicted to caffeine, I was pleasantly surprised when there was a \"strong\" setting. It also has setting for \"Hot Cocoa\" and other which I was also surprised by. Definitely going to purchase some other types of Kcups because of that. In comparison to the Mini, the clearance for cup sizes is more versatile. The Mini can really only accommodate short mugs while I can fit my tall thermos under K250. Overall, it\'s a little bigger than the Keurig Mini but it\'s size is fair in terms of brewing systems. I currently have the black one and it looks great on the countertop. Nothing too flashy. Easy to use because the touch screen prompts you questions. I would definitely recommend!'),
(8716, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-09', 'Love the Colors! This is my first Keurig coffee maker and I love it. I love that I can make anything from coffee to tea to apple cider. love how fast I can make a cup of coffee in the morning. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8717, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-05', 'Garbage! This is the second machine I have gotten (returned the first one) and it does NOT work. It will start to brew and only brews a quarter of a cup each time and that cup is full of grounds!! It then leaves the error message and requires use of the \"maintenance tool\" which doesn\'t fix the problem. Hey I have an idea, how about they fix the actual problem instead of sending a tool where consumers have to use it almost after every use!! I\'ve tried all different kinds of K-cups too with the same results! I HATE this machine!! I\'m retuning it and getting a regular coffee maker. I\'ve had it! Terrible product!'),
(8718, 14, 2, 4, '2015-12-29', 'BLE NDER B IT IS PERFECT FOR SMOOTY OR OTHER COOKING IDEA AS YOU USE IT. THE PRICE IS RIGHT AND THE SHIPPING IS SO PROMPT. I GOT ALL OF MY ORDERS BEFORE CHRISTMAS THAT I LOVE SO MUCH. PUT A BIG SMILE ON MY FACE...'),
(8719, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-16', 'Coffee I love the color and all the only disadvantage is it\'s a little smaller than my old one'),
(8720, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-18', 'Easy coffee in the morning Great for the afternoon one cup of coffee! Use to go out for it. Now we make it at home.'),
(8721, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-24', 'First Keurig and I LOVE Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. This is my first Keurig brewer to purchase and I don\'t think I\'ll ever go back to traditional brewing. I researched for a long time about which brewer was best for me and I decided this one was it! It\'s a bit larger than I expected, but still compact enough to not take over my whole counter. It can be a bit noisy too when brewing. My only real complaint is not having a trusted Eco-pod to refill with my fresh coffee bean. There are some available but with the 2.0 system I\'m not sure if they will work with the smart sensors. Overall, I LOVE my Keurig!'),
(8722, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-23', 'Good machine This is my first time buying and using a Keurig. I bought it bc it\'s just me but during the week I take a travel mug to work and I thought this would work for that but it doesn\'t. It just makes up to 10oz. If it does make 16oz I have not figured it out.'),
(8723, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-06', 'Great coffee maker Purchased as a replacement for an older model and I am totally satisfied. The coffee is hot and tastes awesome. I love the turquoise color and the updated water filter addition. Works wonderful with the resuable kcup I purchased and I can\'t wait to try the carafe mode!'),
(8724, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-05', 'Not what I was hoping for I was so excited to get this keurig on Black Friday but it has sadly been disappointing. Because it offers three different sized coffee holders (cup, travel mug, or carafe) it also takes different sized kcups. If you use a normal sized kcup you only have 6oz, 8oz, or 10oz to choose from on the screen. Thus you can\'t brew a larger cup of coffee from normal sized pod as you can with lesser models. I also received an error message on a random folgers kcup saying it was a knock off and couldn\'t be brewed. I used a gift card so I\'m just going to keep it and get a larger reuseable cup but I wouldn\'t recommend it. I\'d go with a less technologically advanced version.'),
(8725, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-09', 'Didn\'t work out of box Bought this as a gift. We set it up and the Pre-Heating display never goes off. Keurig is sending another one, so we\'ll see. Really poor quality control.'),
(8726, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-31', 'Great coffee brewer I have been using the B70 for years. I bought the 250 mostly for travel. We all know how bad coffee is in the motel rooms. My B70 is still going fine and I plan of using the 250 now to make sure it will be without fault when we travel. I just tried my first cup of tea and it is perfect. Thank you Keurig. Thank you for the free coffee that comes with the machine.'),
(8727, 13, 2, 3, '2015-10-02', 'Liked the older one better I liked the original much better. I got spoiled by the clock and auto turn on/off. This coffee maker doesn\'t have a 12 oz. option. I do like the modernized touch screen.'),
(8728, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Awesome! Target had a great deal regular price 120.00$ and went down to 60.00$ plus a e gift card 15.00$ . I told my friends and family about it and they bought one too! So awesome! Target goes for another win! Thank you Target! My mom loved her Christmas gift!'),
(8729, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-03', 'Christmas gift Bought this for my mom for Christmas since she is a coffee fanatic. In her words, this is perfection!! She says it\'s great and easy to use. She loves the teal color and claims it makes the perfect cup of coffee every time.  The only issue was that it arrived late but customer service refunded my shipping cost.'),
(8730, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Love my new Keurig! I\'ve always wanted one of these, but never could reconcile the cost of the K-cups versus a traditional coffee pot and coffee.  This was on sale so I decided to treat myself for Christmas.  I\'m so glad I did!  It is so easy to set up and maintain, and brews a very good cup of coffee, or tea, or cocoa.  Yes, the K-cups are a little pricey, but it\'s worth it to me.  The Keurig web site offers sample packs of cups so you can try out new flavors before you buy an expensive full sized box.  It\'s a nice red color that matches my kitchen too.  Absolutely recommend.'),
(8731, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-22', 'Love My Purple Keurig! I am very Happy with my new Keurig K250 2.0. Besides looking super stylish this brewer brews a perfect and flavorful cup of coffee everytime. I have and will continue to recommend Keurig to my friends. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8732, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'Great for my kitchen perfect if you want a smaller unit that is easy to use. There is a wide variety of good tasting coffees available . I will receive compensation for this review.'),
(8733, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-31', 'Love it! I love my Keurig 2.0!! Is perfect for my new apartment and my very small kitchen!! Love the fact that it has a touch screen and you have options for other than coffee, the one at my old place didn\'t have that :). I have it in the turquoise color and really love it. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8734, 14, 2, 4, '2015-11-17', 'Blender only This is typically used for crushing frozen fruit to make smoothies. I use it to also make salsa. It works good however, sometimes the machine gets stuck with frozen objects. I try not to overuse it. I use it once in a while. For simple blending it is a great machine but not heavy duty.'),
(8735, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Super + Quiet Great improvement from the Keurig\'s of a few years ago. Very quiet, fast, and it brews a great cup of coffee. I love the fact that you can opt for strong, adjust size of single cup brew, and do a carafe if you choose to. Great price at Target.'),
(8736, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-14', 'Smaller but better! Although I \"downgraded\" in size I feel I upgraded in functionality. The 2.0 is more stylish and is touch screen and VERY easy to use. It\'s very quiet when brewing. The only thing I\'m not crazy about is having to pull my Keurig away from the wall when filling it with water. I tend to make a mess if I don\'t take the water container off the whole unit. Other than that this model is my favorite by far!'),
(8737, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-14', 'Nice coffe maker I bought this coffe maker because I needed one. I saw this one on target and I leve it. It was on sale so I desided to buy it. Over all I like it. The only annoying thing is that it always has to be almost full of water. Otherwise it won\'t work'),
(8738, 13, 2, 3, '2016-01-03', 'missing a lot of features The mashing is good for weekend when time in the mornings are not a factor, without the auto on feature,I don\'t have time to wait for it to heatup. Knowing what I know now I would buy it, I got it for a Christmas gift. This will be my weekend machine. Coffee as always is great but time is a factor for me, back to my older one for the week days.'),
(8739, 13, 2, 4, '2016-02-15', 'Brews fast, but very loud I received this machine as a gift and while it worked just fine I actually upgraded to the 450. It worked well, but was too small for my needs. In a two adult household it seemed like I was refilling the reservoir every day. The reservoir being on the back was a bit cumbersome with the machine being on my kitchen counter underneath cabinets. I had to pull it out and refill the reservoir each time. The motor was also very loud. I called keurig support and they said that over time it would get quieter, but this was just not good for me. It still brewed just fine and the coffee was good. I\'d still recommend to a friend because I do believe that it would work great for someone in a college dorm or military barracks who wants a good cup of coffee without sacrificing on what little counter space you have.'),
(8740, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-04', 'great coffeemaker I love it so much...  real easy life to use that.  taste is just right to me..  i like little strong coffee but depend on what brand of coffee you like.'),
(8741, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-22', 'Great way to enjoy coffee W have used this brewer for about three weeks & it has been great. The different coffee flavors & deciding on what size & strength of brew. This machine has it all.'),
(8742, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-27', 'Very disappointed Very disappointed in the Kuerig 2.0. This is the second one I have bought in 6 months. The first one would not brew a cup of coffee after inserting the pod. Brought it back and continued to use an older Kuerig model ( which I have loved for the pas 8 yrs)which no longer drips water. I bought a second Kuerig and it has an awful plastic taste that will not go away. I have read many reviews and find this is quite common with the 2.0. I also find the 2.0 version very cheaply made compared to the older models. Very disappointed and sad to say I will no longer be a Kuerig user. Making coffee shouldn\'t be this much of a hassle.'),
(8743, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-17', 'Save Your Money The machine will make a cup of coffee occasionally - the rest of the time the machine tells you brew interrupted and you spend the next hour trying to clean the thing out. I have wasted way too many k-cups trying to get a cup of coffee. This Brewer is junk. I have owned other Keurig Brewers and was always a happy customer. I am no longer happy.'),
(8744, 13, 2, 3, '2016-01-01', 'Disappointed I received this model for Christmas to upgrade our older Keurig machine. I love the color, but when I try to brew my favorite kind of coffee, I get the error message, \"Water under pressure\" and it wastes my K-cup. I\'ve had to throw away 5 wasted K-cups in the last 3 days. I\'m taking it back today, but my local store doesn\'t carry that color, so I will have to wait for a new one to be shipped.'),
(8745, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-12', 'Christmas UNsurprise! I ordered this for a Christmas present and it actually came in the Keurig box rather than a Target box.  So needless to say, my son knows exactly what he\'s getting for Christmas... color and all!  ;)'),
(8746, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Love my Keurig I love this coffee machine. I use it just about every day for coffee. My kids use it for hot chocolate. It\'s fast and efficient. Heats up quickly for next user. It works perfectly every time. Thank you!!'),
(8747, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-28', 'LOVE IT!! Our great boss bought us one of these for our office! We love it!! Fresh coffee, tea or cocoa or flavored coffee around the clock! Would recommend this to a friend!'),
(8748, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'LOVE IT!! I got one for my Mom, my son-in-law, a step daughter, and a friend.  We all love our Keurig. It\'s quick and easy to make coffee, cocoa, tea, or a latte.  Easy to work, easy to clean, easy to love!'),
(8749, 13, 2, 2, '2016-12-20', 'Too much is required to get to a cuppa Money$$, counter space, responsiblity for equipments and not enough options for flavor. I like French Roast de-caf and I do not like lukewarm tinted water.  To get to a cuppa I grind my coffee fresh, put it in a filter, pour steaming hot water in it add a little sugar and I am done.  Having said that, why did I go on a hunt to make it easier?  This machine will not accept Peerless coffee k cups.  So, back to the grinder.  They have monopolized themselves out of a place at my kitchen table.  The water needs to be a lot hotter .  Go to McD\'s and for the same money you get the same flavor without the maintenance.  These are good for an office, like many things in my office that I do not want in my kitchen.   I love Target\'s return policy, and the manager of my my local return desk!'),
(8750, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-21', 'Convenience and Style My husband I really enjoy using this Keurig! We previously had a \"mini\" Keurig, but this one has the option for a more varied cup size, such as a full carafe. It also looks much sleeker despite its larger size (it takes up VERY little counter space), and it seems to be quicker at brewing than our previous version. I really like the touch screen-- very convenient. We typically use our Keurig when we want a quick cup of coffee mid-day. My only suggestion would be to allow reusable K-Cups in order to be more environmentally friendly. That was a feature of the Mini Keurig that we really enjoyed.'),
(8751, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-09', 'LOVE THE COLOR - OASIS! This model is an updated version of the machines I had years ago. Coffee isn\'t strong enough.  They never worked right back then. This one seems okay, so far. I also have a Tassimo that makes really good coffee. This one looks nice on my counter. Its okay for the afternoon cup.'),
(8752, 14, 2, 5, '2014-05-08', 'Great blender This is a great blender that actually blends frozen fruit all the way. no chunks.[...] This blender does the job really well, and for the price you cant beat it. i bought it becuase i have purchased several black and decker appliances at target recently, and they are so reliable. Thank you target for having appliances that work and are kind on my wallet!'),
(8753, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-09', 'Love! This is my first Keurig! Love it so far! Set up was real easy...I love that it\'s designed slimmer than the older ones so it doesn\'t take much space.  I don\'t need to insert a pod to dispense hot water! I only wish that it dispensed more than 10 oz.  I have used Folgers pods and it works. I have yet to try with generic store brand.  But, other than that, it\'s great!! Very satisfied with this purchase!'),
(8754, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Brews multiple sizes This machine will brew coffee for 8, 10, 14 and carafe sizes!'),
(8755, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-10', 'Love my Keurig! I love that this machine is compact, since I have limited space. Great colors to choose from, I chose sandy pearl which goes great with my kitchen dcor. My mornings are a bit fast paced, which is why this machine is so great, makes a great cup of coffee fast. Using this machine is easy and convenient. I just love how multifunctional it is and so many varieties of coffee, tea, hot cocoa, etc. to enjoy. I love how you can make hot and iced drinks. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8756, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-11', 'Beware Our family drinks coffee every day and I serve coffee to a roomful of women every Monday. I loved my Keurig Classic but sadly it got tired. I decided to try this bigger one. What a mistake! I\'m always having to clean grounds out of the needle. The reservoir needs refilling at halfway. Most irritating is I have 2 shelves of non-Keurig pods that I now cannot use because this machine won\'t accept them. How chintzy is that! Don\'t buy this one.'),
(8757, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-25', 'Good Product My teenage daughter got this for her birthday and loves it. She doesn\'t need much coffee so I\'m glad it makes single cups. Overall seems like a good product. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(8758, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-31', 'Great Little Coffee Maker I am the only coffee drinker in my household, that\'s why I wanted a single cup coffee maker. After doing my research, I decided I wanted this model. It\'s small enough to not take up a ton of space on my counter, yet not too small that I can\'t use any size cup I choose. The system is really easy to us and easy to clean. I have had no problems with it at all. My only beef with this system is that I have to fill the reservoir, it seems, like every other day. Not a big deal in the realm of things, but nevertheless , a little annoying. I love that I can now have different flavors if I want more than one cup of coffee/tea, and I don\'t have so much coffee left over from traditional brewers. I really do love this model and have been enjoying it every morning.'),
(8759, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'New great tasting coffee quickly and looks good while doing it I was reluctant to pick up and Keurig I had been using my mr. Coffee for years. Finally picked one up at Christmas time while the peices were low.  The machine came packaged well with detailed instructions. Easy setup. Many colors to choose from. I choose sand and it looks really nice on the counter just sitting there. Coffee tastes great.  I also picked up a reusable filter basket and 4 cup crafe so I can use regular non pod coffee as well. Oh and the unit comes with a 50% off pods at Keurigs website and the prices are better than anywhere else even on sale when using the 50% off.  Still keeping my Mr coffee around for when a lot of people are over but for just a cup or 2 I\'ll use my Keurig.'),
(8760, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-28', 'Great Product Even greater variety with this K250. The greatest things about this product for me has been the touch screen and how user friendly it is. My parents are not tech-savvy and it has thus far been very easy for them to navigate.'),
(8761, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-23', 'Happy customer my Mr Coffee broke then to my surprise target was offering a special on kerig...my wishlist coffee maker....I got a great deal on something i have wanted!!!!!'),
(8762, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-27', 'Don\'t Be Late to Work Again This product is convenient and easy to use, making the process to get ready for work faster. Its touch-screen features are a huge plus for today\'s day and age, allowing for easier access and easy ability to brew a cup of coffee. The timeliness of the product is great too; it only takes a few minutes to brew coffee. The only concern I have with the product is that you have to fill the water all the way to a certain line. Sometimes, I would like to just put a cup of water in the machine. However, the product is still great because you could just leave the water in the machine for the next use.'),
(8763, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-12', 'Awesome coffee maker! This is the 2nd Keurig that my husband and I have owned. We have been using this for a few weeks now and the only issue we have run into is not being able to use some older k-cups. It gave us an error message and told us to use Keurig brand k-cups and the k-cups we put in there were! Not sure why it gave that message, but as soon as we put a k-cup that was purchased recently it worked just fine. Also, be aware that the first couple cups of coffee, tea, cocoa, etc. will taste like plastic. The easiest way around that is running hot water through it quite a few times. We also brewed some k-cups that we don\'t drink that often with the hot water. Eventually the taste and smell goes away.'),
(8764, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-06', 'Keurg Fast brewing. Could be hotter.'),
(8765, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-19', 'Love, love , love it I was hoping from the day the 2.0 came out they would make a small one like the K10, and finally, it is there. I ordered with my rewards points and saved quite some money. I have just set it up and used it for the first time, and I am impressed and happy. The turquoise lightens up my counter top, the machine is very quiet, works fast and efficient. I have the K550 to compare, call me a Keurig lover and Keurig collector, but once this K250 will hit the stores, people will go crazy about it.'),
(8766, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Coffee lovers This is my first Keurig and I must say_I am in LOVE! Setup was easy. The screen tells you everything you need to know to operate it. It\'s quick and efficient. Never would I have imagined that I would find a brewer that I absolutely love. Early mornings are made easier with just the touch of a button.'),
(8767, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-31', 'Great for first time Keurig users My husband received for Christmas. Our first Keurig and It is easy to use.'),
(8768, 13, 2, 1, '2015-06-22', 'Comments on new Keurig. Sometimes the reheating stays on for almost an hour. It does several other malfunctions all the time. I\'m sorry we bought it.'),
(8769, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Keurig Coffee Maker Purchased this item for my spouse for Christmas they absolutely love it. Very pleased with the ease of use.'),
(8770, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-19', 'Very dissapointed 6 months ago i bought this keurig, i am now on my 3rd coffee pot. Each time it breaks i call keurig and they just send me a new one. It works for a little while and then it will get stuck preheating, it will stop recognizing k-cups, and then it begins spewing coffee grounds out of the keurig and all over my kitchen. Its not worth the money!'),
(8771, 14, 2, 1, '2014-05-01', 'waste of money!!! My husband and I bought this blender to use for smoothies, milkshakes, etc. I set the blender up and put our fruit in for our smoothie. It immediately started leaking. No sign of it even trying to mash up the fruit.'),
(8772, 14, 2, 1, '2014-09-19', 'Don\'t Buy This Blender! I got this blender last night. Today I tried to make a smoothie. It worked for 1 second, then quit! I double checked the plugs, to make sure it wasn\'t the outlets. I unplugged it, then plugged it back in, tried different settings, etc. It was defective and I\'m returning it today.'),
(8773, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-14', 'Great Coffee Maker I absolutely love Keurig Coffeemakers. I have three and each of my three children have them as well. NOTE: you can use your old k-cups. just tape one of the new k-cup tops to the old ones and they work. I do it all the time. I love fresh coffee each and every cup. LOVE KEURIG!!'),
(8774, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-23', 'Keurig 2.0 I purchased a Keurig 2.0 without the carafe almost a month ago. I owned my previous Keurig for 4 years. I love the new design and brew size choices. It is much quieter than the previous model I owned. I\'m looking forward to buying the carafe and trying it. I also like the option to brew a stronger cup of coffee and the water filter option. If you don\'t think you want the carafe, this model is a great choice!!! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8775, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Love this!! I\'ve always wanted a coffee maker and finally bought one. I am so glad I did. It\'s amazing and wonderful!!'),
(8776, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-12', 'Awesome new release! I was so excited to find out that I was receiving this new Keurig 2.0 k250 brewing system from Influenster, for free! When it came in the mail, I immediately set it up and had to brew a cup of coffee (it came with several k-cups to get you started). I am loving the design, how quiet it is, and the many different settings, including cup size, and coffee strength. I also love that it has a built in filter. I have used it everyday. The only thing I do not like about it is that I previously bought several decaf k-cups because I am pregnant. None of these k-cups work with this new system.'),
(8777, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-13', 'Sleek Design The 2.0 is just as simple to use as the original, but has a much sleeker look and with more options.'),
(8778, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-16', 'I LOVE the touch screen! I absolutely love all of the options that the Keurig 2.0 250 offers! I would recommend it to anyone wanting to upgrade their Keurig to be able to include different sized cups!'),
(8779, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-22', 'We are really liking this! We\'ve had this machine for a couple weeks now and we are really liking it. It is so much nicer to be able to make multiple cups of coffee at one time! We\'ve had no issues at all!'),
(8780, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-21', 'I Love This Product! I have never used a one-cup brewer before, only regular carafe brewers with coffee filters, grounds, etc. This was extremely easy to use even without reading the instructions. I ran into a bit of a problem when the screen would not stop saying \"Add More Water,\" so I went to the instruction booklet and it solved my problem right away. I love the sleek look of the product and it\'s small size because it fits into a corner of my kitchen without taking up much space. The only con I can think of is the amount of time that it takes to preheat, which is not extensively long, but takes maybe 2 minutes before you can brew any coffee.'),
(8781, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Sleek Design I like the sleek design and the compact size of this coffee maker. It does not take up very much counter space in our small kitchen. It makes a very delicious hot cup of coffee and does not cost as much as Starbucks. A very good value for your money.'),
(8782, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-31', 'Best beverage investment ever made!! I absolutely love my Keurig, I will never use anything else! It is so easy to use - and very versatile with what it can make. Coffee, Iced Coffee, Tea, Iced Tea, Hot Chocolate, and Hot Water. Works perfectly, it is a little bit noisy but much quieter than a previous version of Keurig I had. I wouldn\'t trade it for anything else. The only downfall I have is it does take a while to heat the water but I can deal with that. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. Holly'),
(8783, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-13', 'Love my new Keurig! The new Keurig 2.0 is awesome! It works great and takes up less space than my old one. It has a very sleek design with an easy-to-use touch screen. I also love that you can brew a carafe with it! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8784, 14, 2, 1, '2015-05-13', 'burned out blending greens They don\'t make them like they used to. This one only lasted a few months, never even had frozen stuff in it.'),
(8785, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Great Coffee Brewer for the Office This Keurig was purchased for office use. We needed a compact one but this model holds enough water for several cups of coffee before refill. Only drawback is that you can only use Keurig k-cups in it. Price is reasonable, especially if you can purchase it on sale. Seems like it is durable to last a while. So far, we are all happy with the purchase.'),
(8786, 13, 2, 2, '2016-12-23', 'Basic features not available on this model This is my second Keurig. If you want auto on/shut off or the option to set your favorite size this machine is not for you.'),
(8787, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-09', 'Great Brewing System I love this thing! I debated for awhile whether or not to get a Keurig due to the price of K-cups but it was worth it! I like everything about it and the color options were awesome. As far as the price of the k-cups, I have been getting some amazing deals ordering them from Keurig.com and the options are endless!'),
(8788, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Beautiful and functions perfectly. This not only looks great. But the function and easy use it amazing! By the way - Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8789, 13, 2, 4, '2015-12-07', 'Nice Brewer I\'ve been using Keurigs since the first one hit the market all those years ago. After several years of only using the one at my parent\'s or at the office, I decided to get myself the turquoise K200 series to match all my kitchen decor. Love the color! It\'s not as compact at I had hoped, it takes up the same amount of space as my parent\'s older Keurig does, so that makes the amount of usable counter space I have in my small kitchen a bit of an issue. I was surprised by how noisy this unit is as the large commercial unit we have at my office is really quiet, as is the one my parent\'s have. Since I\'ve not had mine for long, I can\'t speak of its longevity, but I can bet it\'ll give me a few years worth of brews. Overall, I\'m very please with my purchase!'),
(8790, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-20', 'RETURNED MINES Very disappointed with my new 2.0 Brewer. Coffee grinds kept getting into my coffee and the water temp wasn\'t hot enough. When making tea I could only chose from 4oz or 6oz of water. So I had to brew twice just to get a 8oz cup of tea. My old k-pods with the keruig stamp on them still wouldn\'t work in this new model. So I wasted about 3 boxes of coffee trying to make them work. I guess I should have stopped while I was ahead, but I told that the old pods would work. Last but not least, who likes to tastes coffee grinds in your coffee? But I must admit that the customer service at Keruig was very nice about my problems and offer to replace the unit at no cost to me, but I decided to return it back to the retail store and pulled the old keruig out of retirement.'),
(8791, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-12', 'Coffee Never Tasted So Amazing! I absolutely love my Keurig 2.0. It\'s perfect for quick and easy on the go coffee. It\'s easy to use, easy to clean, and it\'s a perfect size to put anywhere in the kitchen. The only thing that I don\'t like about it is that is doesn\'t let you make a big cup of coffee, it only offers small cup options.'),
(8792, 13, 2, 1, '2016-09-21', '3rd time should be a charm....... Had loved my Keurig 1 from the day I bought it. Was excited to upgrade to a 2 so I could brew more than 1 cup at a time. Thus I purchased the carafe. It worked once or twice but then started showing \"add more water\" each time thereafter that I attempted to use the carafe. I tried everything but no success. I called customer service and together they through many ways to try to make it work. It continued the message to add more water even though it was full. It was finally decided that I would receive a replacement. Unfortunately the same thing happened. It was replaced again and when I had guests for dinner last week the same thing happened. How embarrassing!!!  This must be happening frequently to other users as well. There is definitely a flaw in the design. I don\'t want another replacement so what do I do with all the carafe size pods that I recently bought?  I am soooo disappointed with the Keurig 2 and will have to start with a new system. Wouldn\'t you expect to receive a refund?'),
(8793, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-13', 'AWESOME!!! I LOVE my new Keurig!! It\'s fast and convenient, and I can just make a cup of coffee on the go! I usually drink coffee throughout the day and now I don\'t have to waste a full pot and worry about whether or not my pot is going to shut off or not. I would definitely recommend this product to a friend!'),
(8794, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Great Deal Waited to get the best deal from Target! Love this keriug and the oasis color matches our other kitchen items.'),
(8795, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-29', 'So Far, So Yummy! I got a Keurig K200 for Christmas. It is way easier to use than my old espresso maker, and I love that I can choose a color other than black or white (yay turquoise!) as well as pick coffee, tea, cocoa, or hot water. The water takes about a minute to preheat from a cold start (only two seconds if it\'s been preheated earlier) and about another minute to completely finish brewing a 10oz K-cup set for strong. The brew size does depend on if you\'re using a cup, mug, or carafe pod (K-cup only goes up to 10oz) however you could do 6oz and 6oz to get a 12oz size, 10oz then 4oz for 14oz, or 10oz and 6oz for a 16oz for the K-cups to get a larger size. Personally I prefer the 10oz K-cup as I like to have room to add cream and sugar or whipped cream without worrying about anything spilling over. Although older K-cups won\'t work in the newer brewers, you could solve the problem by using an accessory like 2.0 My K-Cup to put the older K-cup\'s coffee in or find an equivalent coffee in one of the newer K-cups. So far, I haven\'t had any trouble with coffee grounds in my cup or water spilling into the tray, but I did check my cup sizes first and I wait patiently for it to finish completely. It\'s quite new so I haven\'t had to change the filter or descale yet. I like how the instruction manual covers everything and has a problem solving guide in easy steps. Really the only trouble can be the total cost, as accessories such as the carafe ($20-$30) and 2.0 My K-cup ($15) are not included, as well as storage for the pods ($25-$30), although the cost of the coffee for the maker is much cheaper than the amount I was spending (generally less than $1 per K-cup versus about $5 for one 14-16oz cup). All in all, I\'m very happy with my new (turquoise) Keurig coffee maker!'),
(8796, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-09', 'Love the color I purchased this in the new spa or sea foam color, and it\'s unique and fits my color scheme.  I love Keurig, but the fact that this new style won\'t use the mesh filter coffee pods is a bummer.  I think they are more eco friendly and the older models took them just fine.'),
(8797, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'Easy to use and convenient After having friends and relatives who owned a Keurig, I decided to buy my own. I like how easy it is to use it, but I should have bought a higher model (i.e. K350 maybe) because I have to constantly refill the water. The coffee is not as hot as I remember it to be when drinking from one made with the older model, but nevertheless tasty. I\'m glad I purchased it.'),
(8798, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-22', 'Very happy with my new brewer This is the first brewer I ever bought and I did it because we have one at the office and I lived it so I have to say it is a great product, I\'m very happy with my purchase, it works fast and makes the best coffee everytime (that also depends on the type of cup you buy). After this why not five stars? well its because it is noisy and that I have to be careful about the type of cups I buy because of the DRM, it has to be compatible. I highly recommend it.'),
(8799, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-14', 'Favorite new appliance I\'m not sure how I managed before my keurig 2.0! I love it, it\'s simple to use, mess free, and quick.'),
(8800, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-06', 'Great Keurig! This is my second Keurig. A much better technology than the mini-plus. I do wish I would\'ve bought the larger model that comes with a carafe. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8801, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-28', 'Keurig 200 This was a Christmas gift for our son in law. The delivery process was a disaster which may have been my fault.   However, my son in law has used it once and said it was easy to use and the coffee was great'),
(8802, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-20', 'I am in love I have used the Keurig in the past when it first came out and I was pretty impressed. I had a small one but that one unfortunately broke. I stop by Dunkin Donuts every morning to pick myself up a Medium HOT Latte. Well let me JUST SAY_NOT ANYMORE. Go pick yourself up Keurig 2.0 immediately! Some may think I am crazy but I brought my Keurig 2.0 to work to share with my co-workers. I also purchased the reusable pod so I can pack whatever coffee I like versus buying the pods. Compare my $3+ daily run from Dunkin or getting a box of 12 pods for $8.00 which equals out to .67 cents a day_which route would you choose? Honestly speaking, I was so used to Dunkin Donuts that I thought I liked it! Well after taking a week break from Dunkin and then picking one up on the way home one afternoon (It was a long day at work) I was so unhappy. I needed my coffee from my Keurig. I have seen and read reviews about the old K-Cups not working on the 2.0 versions. I have not had an issue. I bought my reusable pod but I have also used K-Cups from the 1.0 and it worked just as fine on the 2.0. I love this Coffee Machine and I am looking forward to purchasing another one. I will need it for my home! I will purchase the Carafe with it this time.'),
(8803, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-24', 'Upgrade from my Keurig Vue I recently purchased my keuig 2.0 using my keurig points as an upgrade from my keurig vue. I have only had it for a short while but I\'m already in love with it. I love how versatile it is by being able to use k-cups or the carafe cups. And there are such a variety of choices with the k-cups unlike the vue cups. I ordered my keurig 2.0 in the turquoise color, and I love it\'s bright, vibrant, and color. At this time, I have no cons at all about my new keurig 2.0 machine. I\'m very pleased with it.'),
(8804, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'It\'s so pretty It looks great on my counter and it\'s easy to use.'),
(8805, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-29', 'nice brewer thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review. i love this brewer purchased less than a week ago. easy to brew and very convenient to use for daily use. the carafe is easy to use but sometimes i feel the coffee brewed in carafe mode is not very strong. personal size is excellent and i love it.'),
(8806, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-29', 'Great upgrades from the original! We purchased the original Keurig when it first came out, and used it for quite some time. Now we have this version, and are impressed with the upgrades and better features than the original model. Pros: Quietso much quieter than the first version. Lots more options when brewing. You can opt for a \"strong\" brew, change the amount of water used, or (my favorite) just heat water! Love that feature for brewing tea. This version has a carafe that you can fill with using special pods. I\'d love to try this out for brewing a large quantity, but it was not included with my package. This version is also smaller than the original. Love that saved counter space. I love that you can descale your machine. We had the original version of the Keurig and this was not something that was mentioned/recommended (if I remember right). Such a great way to keep your machine running great. Cons: The water chamber signals needing to be refilled when it still has 1/3 of the water left in it. At our house, my husband and I drink multiple cups of coffee each day, so it needs to be refilled frequently. The coffee is not equal to a strong cup you\'d get from an espresso machine (which is what we use to make coffee prior to getting this Keurig.) But, if you like coffee, don\'t need a crazy strong brew (even with the strong feature), this machine is quiet, easy to clean, and easy peasy to use. Such a great product (especially when comparing to the original one!).'),
(8807, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-29', 'New Technology I currently have a Kuerig. It is several years old and is used multiple times on any given day. It seems to be wearing out and has experienced a few hiccups lately. Thought I would by a replacement before it just dies. However, I choose not to be limited to \"kuerig\" sanctioned beverages. I will find another brand single beverage brewing systems that does not impose limits to personal preferences.'),
(8808, 13, 2, 5, '2016-02-01', 'Keurig is the Bomb..... This coffeemaker is the best on the planet!!!! I love it, it\'s top shelf. Nothing even comes close, I love, love, love it!!! Thank you Keurig!!!!'),
(8809, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-03', 'Kuerig 2.0 K200 is terrible The product malfunctions every time I use it. The Brewer water is under too much pressure every time, and I get coffee grounds in every cup. I haven\'t even had the model replaced three times. All three machines gave me the same results. If you are looking for a reliable coffee maker, this is not the one.'),
(8810, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-24', 'awesome flavors I just want to say , \"Thank You Keurig\" .  Waking up in the morning time, with a hot cup of Hazelnut Cappuccino , is such a blessing.  I love my Keurig 250  machine. It is such a great time of season too , since Keurig has any flavor that I can think of. Wonderful scent of Autumn in the house , as I brew a cup of pumpkin spice. Mmmmmmm.  Happy Holidays Keurig !');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8811, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-11', 'Problem Bought one on December 6th and it stopped working on December 9th. The display showed \"sorry brew interrupted\". I followed the instructions in the manual and still couldn\'t get the machine to work. I brought it back to the store where I purchased it last night and got another. Hoping that there will be no problem with this one!'),
(8812, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-18', 'Great coffee maker and goes well with kitchen decor Had this coffee maker for over 2 weeks. Haven\'t had a problem yet. Works great and the bright teal color goes great in my kitchen. The only reason I didn\'t give it 5 stars is I\'ve had to refill the water more frequently than my last keurig. Can\'t complain though. Great color and great coffee!'),
(8813, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-03', 'SAVE YOUR MONEY AND HAIR! This is, without any doubt the most expensive way to waste your money. I drink no more than 3 cups a day and this thing has been failing to work as advertised since month 2. My personal favorite is the completely white screen that doesn\'t allow you to do ANYTHING., and Keurig\'s helpful response? Please unplug and \"hopefully that will solve the problem\" and the good news is that it does for about 3 cups of coffee. Oh, and sometimes even unplugging it does not work. On top of that, the reliability of the machine is about 20%, each day is a new adventure on what won\'t work on this machine. Some days it takes (no exaggeration) 20minutes to \"preheat\" , and at least once a week it won\'t produce a full cup of coffee (no matter how often or well you use their little unclogger thing). Add to this you can\'t use any pods except those made by/for Keurig and that you can\'t dispense more than 6 oz of hot water at a time (go hang, tea drinkers!) and that the water filter required is an extra 20 bucks, and what you have is an overpriced trashcan ornament. Keruig, complete fail. I\'ll be taking my business elsewhere. Between the lousy equipment and your lackluster\"customer service\" I\'ll never purchase a Keurig product again. Happy New Year to me. *Note: I\'d have used stronger language about my disgust for the machine and Keurig\'s customer service, but the site won\'t even allow it. Have no doubt, this is the worst piece of equipment I\'ve run across. Don\'t waste your time, money and save keep your hair in your head where it belongs.'),
(8814, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-30', 'Do you believe in LOVE at first cup? I had always wanted a keurig but thought they were kind of pricey so I pushed it off until my Mr. Coffee finally gave up :(. I read every single review on this which was probably the best and worst thing I did because some of these reviews were harsh and seriously convinced me not to purchase this. I was too excited for the keurig that I had to just experience it myself.  So, this coffee machine is amazing. It makes a delicious cup of coffee but You CAN NOT use pods that are not k-pods but there is a hack for it if you go online, (If this is a problem for you then just invest in a different coffee maker) However you can use your own ground coffee if you purchase the reusable pod, which I bought at target as well(It\'s a purple one). I LOVE THIS because I like buying my own ground coffee and you save a lot of money. (1 lb of coffee is approx 46 cups if you do 2 tbls for every 6 oz of water).  It has an option for strong coffee and hot cocoa which is pretty cool. Also, you can do a carafe :D yes a whole carafe!!! The only bummer is that It is sold separately ($20.00) :( and they are very limited on flavors but not to worry you can also buy a reusable pod for it.  If this review still has you doubting about the item then just BUY it!!! You wont regret a think'),
(8815, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-19', 'I love the Keurig 2.0 K250! I had a Keurig K45 Elite before receiving the 2.0 K250, so I was already a huge fan. Now, I am an even bigger fan! This brewer provides the same great tasting, easy to make coffee as the original with added features. My favorite is that I can make a personal cup for myself or a carafe for guests.'),
(8816, 14, 2, 1, '2015-12-24', 'Broke second time I used it Horrible, do not buy! This blender broke the second time I used it. Complete waste of money.'),
(8817, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-13', 'Best way to make coffee I started use this keurig at work amd had to get one for myself at school! I love it because its so fast and simple, not too much of a mess either. I love that in comes in different colors so you can personalize it and all the different flavored kcups available, I just wish they weren\'t so pricey!'),
(8818, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Absolutely love it!! I\'ve owned this keurig for over a year now and it has treated me well. I recommend this to starters who are looking for a decent keurig system. It\'s amazing!'),
(8819, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Happy with the upgade! I am happy with my upgrade to a carafe brewer; I love the option to brew a cup weekdays and make a pot on the weekends!'),
(8820, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-15', 'My newest obsession I used a traditional coffee maker in the past and never saw the use for this type of brewer. I believe I packed my coffee maker away after my 2nd brew with this Keurig. It\'s so easy to use, and there is nothing to clean up. I love that this brewer makes a single serving and I can chose the option of making a strong cup. The hot water dispense is another great feature. It looks great on my countertop alongside my other stainless steel appliances. I was told this was the smaller brewer of this system however I consider this thing to be huge. I had to contact customer service which was another great experience. They actually returned my call, addressed my issue and followed up afterwards.'),
(8821, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-19', 'Constant error on display Right out of the box I got an error saying too much water pressure and to perform maintenance. I performed the maintenance 5 times and still got the error. I\'ve owned the non digital Keurig and trust me they are much better. Also to use non Keurig licensed k cups you need to buy a \'freedom clip\' from eBay or Amazon. Allows you to use any k cup. I finally got it to work by pushing the pod down very firmly before closing the lid. Too much trouble. Buy the k50'),
(8822, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-02', 'We Are Brewin\'!! I love it!! There are tons of varieties. I just wish I could get more than 6oz of hot water at a time. I find myself choosing the 6oz and then going back and choosing the 4oz just to make a decent size cup of hot water.'),
(8823, 13, 2, 2, '2016-05-15', 'Returning my Keurig I bought the Keurig to replace my coffee maker of a different brand. I was familiar with Keurig\'s however because we\'ve always had one at work. First thing I realized: there aren\'t 9 sizes as advertised! I was excited about making a larger cup of coffee... but no go. Second the machine is loud. Why? And since I can only make a 10oz cup, why do I have to put so much water into the water reservoir? Lastly, what\'s the deal with the filter that is in the package, but mentioned no where in the instructions? So weird and incomplete. My coffee was good, but for the money, I want a product that was advertised and as good as the older models I\'ve used in the past at work. I\'m taking my K200 back.'),
(8824, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-01', 'New Keurigs Great updated coffeemaker to use in my kitchen! Little disappointed some of my legit k-cup pods do not work in it.'),
(8825, 13, 2, 4, '2016-10-26', 'Great cup for the casual drinker. This is my first Keurig.  It works well and yes, does accept the off-brand reusable pods I purchased.   Pros: It makes a single cup, which is about all each of us ever drink.  The pods are easy to rinse and there is no used coffee ground smell to deal with.  So, no waste.  The coffee is brewed to drinking temperature - no waiting, blowing, or burnt tongues.    Cons: It\'s probably not a good choice for coffee snobs as it brews quickly and at a lower temperature.  I *am* a tea snob and it definitely does not brew hot enough for a good cup of tea.    The Oasis color does show splatter so often needs a wipe-down after use.  Otherwise, we love it as we only make what we drink and have very little cleanup afterward!'),
(8826, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-05', 'Love my Keurig 2.0 K250! I love this Keurig. At first I was a little confused, but once I read the directions(I have used an older model) I had no problems. I love the touch screen, I think it makes it easier. There are tons of pods to choose from. The only thing I am not a fan of is that so much water has to be kept in it at all times. I only drink coffee a few days a week, so this is perfect for me. I think this would make a great gift for anyone.'),
(8827, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-22', 'Love it! Love this coffee machine. Easy to use and easy to set up!'),
(8828, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'We love it! My family uses it for iced tea, lemonade, hot chocolate, and whatever else we could want. It\'s nice to be able to make a single cup of something instead of making a whole pot or pitcher.'),
(8829, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-28', 'Poor experience We have a luxury cabin in the mountains of Colorado that we rent out when not using it personally. We know how important coffee is to our guests (and us!), so we bought this coffee machine for them with a supply of various types of coffee so everyone would be able to enjoy their favorite as they watch the sun rise on the Rockies. This water reservoir was awkward for our cabinet situation, which we didn\'t take into consideration when we bought the machine, not a fault of the Keurig at all. But, this machine received minimal usage as our cabin was unoccupied for most of the 2 months we owned it. On our next visit to the cabin, the machine began spitting out water, filling cups half way, and then quit working. Thankfully, our guests were not inconvenienced by this faulty product! We\'ve had Keurigs at home and at the office for years, and they\'ve been true workhorses and are still going strong. Our cabin is located in a remote area of Colorado and we had to replace the faulty machine (during an EPIC snow event, even by Colorado standards) with another brand of machine to accommodate incoming guests. I did return the defective machine to the store it was purchased and received a refund, so I\'m not complaining about anything except the design flaws and major inconvenience of this product.'),
(8830, 13, 2, 3, '2015-10-05', 'keurig 2.0 0n my 3rd keurig in 5 months. they just stopped working. finally bought a mr coffee brewer which also has keurig name on it/ have had it 3 weeks. sure hope it lasts more than a month. am very disappointed in keurig. it used to have such a good name!'),
(8831, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-23', 'Good machine Overall good machine so far. The one complaint I have is the resivour. We use the fridge water and when filling it always makes a mess. It\'s oddly shaped. Other than that it makes a smooth cup of coffee.'),
(8832, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'Great brewer! This is my first Keurig. I got it after my wife and I had our first child. She wanted decaf coffee and I didnt want to have to make two pots every morning. Brews a great cup of coffee. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8833, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-08', 'Beautiful color and nice features I purchased this Keurig in the turquoise color and it is really a beautiful addition to the kitchen. I do like all of the features and touch screen but I do wish it would make a larger cup than the 10 ounces. I am hoping that Keurig has all the problems figured out and this one lasts longer than my previous Keurig!'),
(8834, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Best coffee maker- EVER!! This is for my daughter\'s Christmas gift because her other one is getting old and this one is bigger and better! She will love it!!!'),
(8835, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-31', 'New to Keurig Not as good as fresh brewed coffee but great for single cups. One early snag, the needle that punctures the top of the K-cup can get clogged and needs to be cleaned out with a paper clip to brew another cup. But no worries, there are many y-tube videos that show how to fix the problem and BB&B ...(read more)'),
(8836, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Great coffee maker! Installation was simple and it came with helpful instructions on how to setup, clean, and care for your Keurig. This Keurig is a little small, but perfect for an apartment as it saves space. I would recommend it to anyone, and I especially love the nice white color! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8837, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-16', 'Love this new Brewer. Keurig does it ag First I have to say I\'ve been a Keurig customer for several years. I have one of the original Keurigs and recently bought a 2.0 K550. I received the 2.0 K250 system complimentary to test and review. This smaller system is great. Its very compact so it doesn\'t take up a lot of counter space. This smaller version has a water reservoir which is great instead of needing to pour water in for each cup. The screen walks you through set up and is extremely easy to use. You can select from different cup sizes to strengths and even brew a carafe. This also came with a ton of K-Cups to try, the descaling cleaner and the Keurig maintenance tool. I have noticed with these new 2.0 systems, especially with my K550 the needles get clogged about every other day and have to be cleaned with the provided tool. One of the things that I was really impressed with is that I have seen several reviews where people didn\'t know they couldn\'t use their existing K-cups with the new 2.0 system. Keurig included a post card that said if you have any to contact them and they will replace them. Customer service doesn\'t get much better than that.'),
(8838, 14, 2, 3, '2015-09-21', 'May return this because the blades are weird The shape of the blades may do what it is supposed to do -- crush ice? -- but it doesn\'t work like a regular blender in that it doesn\'t seem to create a vortex that drags down the unblended stuff on the top to get blended. Not too happy with it but I can\'t seem to find a basic blender like the Sunbeam I had that finally wore out.'),
(8839, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Coffee Shop Misses Me I bought my Keurig in attempt to save some money at the local coffee shop. So far it has worked. I use my Keurig every morning before I head out the door. It\'s quick and convenient. The compact size works great on the limited counter space that I have. The only downside, I can not fit my travel mug under the machine. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8840, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-13', 'Super convenient! Love this machine. It is well built and super easy to use. It makes an really good, hot, and easy cup of coffee. My complaint is that it will not allow you to brew a cup of coffee with more than 10 oz of fluid. Such a bummer.'),
(8841, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-14', 'Fresh Coffee at the Office My wife can now have a fresh cup of coffee at the office whenever she wants and won\'t have to carry a thermos back and forth. Great product. It\'s both easy and fast.'),
(8842, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-19', 'Works like a charm! Bought this when I decided that morning coffee was too important to shove aside due to lack of time! Set up instructions were helpful, the machine itself is user friendly, it works great, and it it adds a pop of color to the kitchen! Perfect for my small apartment. Thanks, Keurig!'),
(8843, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-17', 'Great coffee maker! Glad our household finally made the switch to Keurig. We had been using a Scoop single serve machine for years but it was beginning to fail. It makes a great cup of coffee and looks super cute as well. It\'s well made and easy to wipe down. Very happy with my purchase.'),
(8844, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-01', 'Great starter Keurig I bought this for my boyfriend. He is not an everyday coffee drinker so he didn\'t need anything fancy. He says it works well and is enjoying it.'),
(8845, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'K200 I bought this on black Friday. It is super easy to use. I bought the keurig coffee pot and the reusable coffee filters to make pots of coffee or single cups with regular bagged coffee. It\'s so convenient.'),
(8846, 13, 2, 4, '2016-09-22', 'Love my New 2.0 Keurig My larger Keurig went out and really like this smaller unit and the bone color is perfect in my newly updated kitchen.'),
(8847, 13, 2, 1, '2015-06-16', 'I had two of your Brewing systen, return them because it wou system did not work for me, I being a mature lady thought I had not follow the instruction wrong call your CSR She told me what to do. Worked firs,t next several did not brew.'),
(8848, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-16', 'Great Brewer! Awesome Machine LOVE, LOVE, LOVE!!! This Keurig is a great asset to any home. I like the fact it has a water filter and the automatic on/off setting. I\'m an ample coffee drinker now that I work 12 hr shifts so my morning brew is a must. I also like my tea in the evening which I can make all with just this machine. Overall great product from a great company!'),
(8849, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-17', 'Coffee just got better! My husband and I LOVE this machine! It has improved upon the older edition Keurig we had but including more cup sizes as well as a specific hot water dispensing option. We use it every morning for our coffee (he likes flavored coffee whereas I don\'t so Keurig is perfect for us) and I make a lot of hot tea in the afternoon evenings. The only think I did not like about it was when using non-2.0 k-cups, the cup sizes are limited.'),
(8850, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-31', 'Good brewer. Like the product. Easy to use and quiet. Would have given 5 stars, however, this brewer lacks automatic shut-off. Disappointed that this feature was not included. I believe this is the only Keurig brewer that does not this feature.'),
(8851, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-22', 'We love our Keurig! Our Keurig is easy to use, quick preheat time and the coffee always tastes great. My husband uses the strong setting for his coffee and it says that is tastes better than any other coffee pot he has had coffee out of. P.S. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8852, 13, 2, 4, '2016-03-28', 'Convenience! My mother has one of the first Keurigs that came out, have always enjoyed the coffee so I got one myself....coffee is delicious! Need hot water for a cup of tea, hot chocolate, you got it. Only BAD thing is I ordered a variety pack of K-cups on the internet, some do not work with my machine. Plus, it would be nice if Keurig would send a starter sample of K-cups to get started. All-in-all, great machine.......so far!'),
(8853, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-11', 'Great brewer! When we moved we had to leave our Keurig behind. I found the orange K250 and it fit our new decor perfectly. We love the \"strong\" choice and the selection of different sizes and ease of hot water for tea or hot chocolate. The only problem is that I can\'t register it at this site! There is no choice for K250! ;-('),
(8854, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Keurig Got this for my mom for Christmas. She loves it'),
(8855, 13, 2, 2, '2016-07-31', 'Not my favorite krurig maker! I bought this as a replacement to my first Keurig maker that lasted over 4 years!  I am not as pleased with this one!  I wish that I had paid more attention to the size of the water reservoir tank!!  While 40oz sounds like a lot, it is not.  I\'m constantly having to add water!! Trust me, for that \"first\" morning cup, especially waking up for work.... You don\'t want to read that dreaded message \"add more water\".  If you drink at least 3 cups of coffee a day - you will be disappointed in this maker due to the size of the water tank.  While I love Keurig makers, I\'m stuck with this one until it wears out.  Choose another model for all  you true coffee lovers!!'),
(8856, 13, 2, 5, '2016-08-03', 'Great coffee Just received this today. Still trying to get used to using it but my first cup of coffee was awesome. I love the color too'),
(8857, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-08', 'Learning as I Go Twice daily. Enjoy the speed in the morning. I do continue to try to find a less strong blend.'),
(8858, 13, 2, 2, '2016-04-23', 'Not all that happy I use this product every day and have had this model for about a month. I am not happy with the choice of cup size to be brewed. Also, it is very noisy. The coffee tastes OK but is stronger than I like it since I was used to brewing a larger cup size. Can\'t recommend it.'),
(8859, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-02', 'Digital junk many times a day. First time it gives me a stupid message \"OOOPS\" it is going in the trash.'),
(8860, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-12', 'System upgrade! Easy to use overall. Wish it heated up quicker and started brewing on its own.'),
(8861, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-28', 'Does not work.....punches hole in the mesh filter This machine punches a hole in the mesh filter inside the Kcup and allows all the coffee ground to end up in your cup of coffee. DO NOT BUY THE K200 2.0 version.'),
(8862, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'BEST Keurig Ever! I use this every day! it is the best Keurig I have had. I love the ease of using it and how I can control the cup size for my one cup, or fill a carafe and enjoy coffee with my mother. The carafe also keeps the coffee warm for a very long time, which is even better! Best Keurig Ever!'),
(8863, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-27', 'Great New Product! I absolutely love this new Keurig! I am someone who drinks tea at least once a day so I need something quick, that has multiple settings for my variety of mugs and k-cups. This Keurig is better than one I had in the past since it\'s much more quiet, I can make tea without having to worry about waking my roommates up. In addition to this, the water heats up and disperses quickly so when I\'m on the run to work I can quickly grab some tea without worrying about being late. It also accepts a wide variety of k-cups which is very nice to know I won\'t have to go out and buy a new set. Lastly, the design of the Keurig is great because it\'s sleek and fits almost anywhere, it\'s not as bulky as some have been in the past. Overall I think this is a fantastic product and I would without a doubt recommend it to friends and family.'),
(8864, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-10', 'Kerrigan K200 Coffe Maker The product is pleasing to the eye, easy to operate and of good quality; competitive price.'),
(8865, 13, 2, 1, '2016-04-09', 'Junk is the only thing that comes to mind Got this as a gift had nothing but problems. Brew is under pressure then blows up the k cup grounds and coffee running all over.Called and they gave me a new on and the third cup did the same thing. I guess going to the gas station is the best way to get a cup of coffee. My suggestion DO NOT BUY THIS ONE!!!! Wish some one would have told my father in law.'),
(8866, 14, 2, 5, '2015-07-03', 'Buy It!! I had purchased the Montel Williams blender some years back.. I paid 400$ for that thing and had to throw it out due to them discontinuing making the jar. I needed to replace the plastic jar because it started leaking. After some research, I decided to spend the least amount on a blender. I read the reviews, loved the price and the fact that its a glass jar. I really love this blender... I cannot believe how well it blends (I think even better than the Montel one). The major plus is how easy it is to clean.. the parts come off easily. Another plus is that it is a GLASS jar.. so much cleaner than plastic. I definitely recommend this blender...'),
(8867, 13, 2, 3, '2016-04-27', 'A little disappointed Slightly disappointed by this brewer. Judging by info on the outside of the box, stating nine brew sizes, I assumed I would be able to brew a large mug of coffee. Come to find out, Keurig now requires K-Mug pods in brew to get a 12, 14, or 16 oz. much of coffee. Never mind, you can work your way around this by brewing a 10 oz. size and then brewing another 4 oz. using the same regular k-cup. Keurigs are nice as far as being quick to brew, but kind of aggravating that in order to get a full mug of coffee, I have to go out and spend more for the special pods. No thanks.....I\'ll just brew twice and save myself some money.'),
(8868, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-10', 'Happy Girl I currently own 3 kuerg\'s. A large older madel for my home, a mini for the office and this one for my workweek condo. I needed a full size slender unit for the micro kitchen in this rental- this is PERFECT. in every way! Ability to brew different sizes and strengths, redesign of the pod system (genius), digital display ....this is a classy redesign on my most necessary workhorse of an appliance! Thank you kuerg! I would not only recommend this machine, I\'m purchasing one for a sister in law as a housewarming gift!'),
(8869, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Great buy! Love the color! Personalize the size and strength of coffee too!'),
(8870, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-23', 'Renewed my love of coffee This is a huge improvement over their smaller Keurigs. You can choose more cup sizes and it has the optional Carafe you can buy to make a pot of coffee. It also has a hot water feature and a reservior so you don\'t have to fill it up everytime you want to make coffee. I like how you can have different coffees all the time and not have to worry about using up one bag of coffee before opening another. It is especially handy to have with different coffee drinkers in the house who like different things. The single-serve K Cups also ensure your coffee is always fresh. Though definitely not a deal-breaker, one con is that that I wish you could brew more than 10 oz without having to use the Carafe pods. For instance, 10 oz doesn\'t fill up a large coffee mug or travel mug, and I don\'t want to make a whole pot just for those. Also the product is a little more wasteful than traditional coffee since you are using a disposable K Cup each time, and I\'m not sure if my recycling company wants me throwing in the bin the pods with used coffee grounds in them. However, the Keurig\'s benefits outweigh these concerns, and it has already replaced my old way of making coffee. I find myself drinking coffee/tea more often and at different times of the day than I had before. It brews much faster than my old traditional coffee pot, and the hot water feature makes non-K Cup hot chocolate or tea 10x faster than boiling water on the stove. I cannot review the K Pods or Carafe since I do not own a carafe (yet), but I\'m sure it would still be faster to brew than a traditional pot. Overall, this is a great product, and although I was initially skeptical on its practicality, I can\'t imagine not using it.'),
(8871, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-13', 'I Really Like the Keurig 2.0 K250 Brewing System I have to start by saying that the Keurig is fairly large and takes up quite a bit of counter space which can be a bit of a problem if you have limited counter space. The K-cups also take up a lot of room regardless of whether you store them on the counter or in a cabinet; and again, if you have limited counter/cabinet space that can be a bit of a problem. When brewing your coffee/tea, the Keurig is a little noisy, but it\'s not terribly loud. The K-cups are convenient, but they are really bad for the environment so you have to take the time to recycle! With that being said, I do have to say that the instructions for the Keurig are super simple to follow, it is really easy to clean, it is really easy to brew your coffee/tea. The thing I like the most about the Keurig is that it is extremely fast at brewing your coffee/tea. This is great, especially when you are in a hurry and rushing out the door! Overalll, I really like this product and highly reccommend it!'),
(8872, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-26', 'First Time Keurig User Finally joined the Keurig world and can\'t believe I didn\'t do it sooner! Love brewing a cup everyday and carafe on the weekends! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8873, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Keurig love it and got at a good price!!! Super easy to use!!!'),
(8874, 13, 2, 4, '2015-12-20', 'Love the new colors Love the color choices, we picked white to match our kitchen and it takes inches off the visual impact of the machine. Who says black makes you look thin? Only wish the cord color matched the unit color.'),
(8875, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-16', 'Very nice machine This is amazing. It is very thin, but deep. You can\'t tell by the pics but it is twice as deep (from front to back) than it is wide. I like pretty much everything about it. Makes coffee very fast and is just an all around well built machine'),
(8876, 13, 2, 2, '2015-11-01', 'Not So Happy! The First KEURIG wouldn\'t Work. Got the Replacement, it has A VERY ODD TASTE TO IT, RAN ALOT OF WATER THROUGH IT, SOMEWHAT BETTER. BUT STILL NOT AS GOOD AS MY CHEAP COFFEE MAKER. SUPPOSE TO HAVE GOTTEN A FEE BOX OF COFFEE, ENTERED THE PROMO CODE, SHOPPING CART SHOWED FREE, THEN ON MY ORDERS, IT SHOWED AS AN ERROR AFTER THE SHOPPING CART SHOWED THAT IT WOULD BE SHIPPED, SO GUESS I DO NOT GET THAT EITHER.'),
(8877, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Purple keurig It was a great surprise and a big hit with the person wee bought it for!'),
(8878, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-13', 'Amazing!!!! This is my first Keuring and I am happy I have it. :) makes it extremely easy to make a cup of coffee. I think I am drinking more coffee at home now that I have one. LOL Before making a cup took many steps. Now all I do it add water, insert the k-cup, select the amount of coffee to dispense, and the machine does the rest. There is a function that makes the coffee stronger, if that is your preference. THE ONLY THING I don\'t like about it is the fact THERE IS NO ESPRESSO function. Now it did allow me to make 4OZ cup of coffee that was SUPER strong. However it is not like an expresso. If anyone has had Cuban coffee then you know what I mean. All in all this is a awesome machine for any home. If I were you, I would consider investing in one.'),
(8879, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Dorm Room Perfect! As a college freshman and being a huge coffee drinker, I needed to make that I had a reliable source of coffee each morning. I took the liberty upon myself to buy a Keurig for not only myself but also my roommates. I was going to do it sooner or later so I chose sooner. I bought mine in white and looks great; although I do have to clean it often to keep it white. The Keurig is super sleek and doesn\'t take up too much room in my dorm. The touch screen is nice and simple. It\'s really easy to navigate and make different cups of coffee. My dorm mates love it as well because all of us just buy our own coffee and make our own cup of joe in the morning. Though the system reads the K-Cups and only accept K-Cups, it\'s not much a problem for me since I usually buy K-Cups from the Keurig site. All in all, I love my Keurig. It does its job well and I hope for many cups of coffee to come! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8880, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-14', 'Happy with my Keurig! Have been using Keurig for years, but this is the first one I\'ve personally owned. Although the coffee isn\'t the same quality as you\'d get from a french press, it\'s convenient and has been reliable so far!'),
(8881, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-24', 'The Perfect Brewer My family and I love our new Keurig 2.0. It is very versatile, we are able to brew multiple cup sizes and both hot and cold beverages. Another plus is it saves time during our busy mornings. With the push of a button our coffee or tea is done! I received( or will receive) compensation/free product for my unbiased review.'),
(8882, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-14', 'It\'s a Keurig It is what you expect, a Keurig.'),
(8883, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-22', 'Fast, Fun, Fresh tasting Coffee Keurig 2.0 machine promises that it will make my coffee in less than a minute! So I pop in a Breakfast Blend, close it and press brew! VOILA! Fresh coffee in my cup. Hay Now! I am so excited ans my kids are very impressed at not having me make them late for school again. No more waiting on my coffee. My first taste test was great, I was worried about the pods not being fresh. I am used to grinding my own beans and keeping them in the freezer. But I was pleasantly surprised. Fresh tasting coffee. I do like coffee a bit strong, so on my next brew, I pressed the \'strong\' button! I loved it and will have to always remember to press that. By the time I used the Keurig the 5th time, it was not working. I put in three different pods, and it was only dripping. I was devastated! But, I decided to read the cleaning directions and I used the little orange thingy to remove buildup in the machine. And Hallelujah it worked. Overall I love the Keurig. I do need to start a small saving for my pods, because they are a bit expensive.'),
(8884, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-22', 'Magical machine It\'s so simple, so clean and so easy to use. Coffee, tea or hot cocoa is brewed and ready to drink in about 30 seconds. LOVE IT! Also the little metal coffee pod drawers that target sells make storing the pods under the machine nice and neat. Thanks keurig for the free pods for this review!'),
(8885, 13, 2, 2, '2015-09-13', 'Not a happy customer I\'ve wanted a Keurig for a whle now and got one for my birthday. I love the conveience of being able to brew one cup. However, I do find the \"pod coffee\" to be much more expensive so I thought it would be great to buy the coffee holding pod so I could use my own coffee. Evidently not possible on the 2.0. What a bummer. I\'m very disappointed. My friends have older brewers which do hold off market pods where you can use your own coffee. I\'m thinking Keurig got smart and now doesn\'t allow that. Wow. Good job on that one, but I\'m not a happy customer. Tried searching on Keurig site for one, can\'t find it. Again, not a happy customer.'),
(8886, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-19', 'Disappointed - Celestial Tea K-cups are not compatible I was very disappointed to learn that the Celestial Seasonings Herbal Tea K-Cups were not compatible with this model. They worked just fine with my old Cuisinart Keurig machine. Would not have bought it if I had known.'),
(8887, 13, 2, 3, '2015-06-13', 'Bit disappointed with the features on my K250 I upgraded to the K250 after having one of the recalled mini\'s. I was waiting for the K250 rather than just get another mini because I was reading the features and really wanted bigger cup sizes. First of all if you are using a regular k-cup you only get 4 cup sizes, 4/6/8/10. I was hoping to go to at least 12oz for my bigger mugs. I cannot see a way to do that unless using a carafe. There are very limited options on the screen. I do not have a carafe but presumably when you remove the tray and insert a carafe you get more options? It\'s not a bad looking unit but also if I leave it plugged in like my two older keurigs it does actually stay on with the water heated. I don\'t like that. I don\'t want to have to unplug every time (because I know I will forget) and I feel it dangerous to leave heated all day long. The only advantage I see right now is that I can fit bigger mugs in without having to remove the drip tray - but I can\'t fill them. I am sure the carafe would solve a few of my issues but it doesn\'t come with the K250, you have to purchase it. Looking at the reviews (about not keeping warm) and the pictures I have seen I am not sure a plastic carafe would be worth the extra money. Sorry, I love my coffee and wouldn\'t be without my one cup brewer (I have a keurig at home and in my office, I even take them away with me if I am out of town) but I had higher expectations of this model.'),
(8888, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Coffee never tasted so good! I was given my Keurig for my Birthday a few weeks ago and I have never been happier. My husband bought me the turquoise one and the color just pops in my kitchen. The set up was easy and within 10 minutes I was already brewing my first cup of coffee. I love the varieties of coffees, teas and hot chocolates they have for the Keurig. I love having options on what I want to drink. I haven\'t had any problems with my coffee maker thus far, but I\'m sure if I do, customer service would take care of me. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8889, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-17', 'First time buyer First Keurig, and I\'m glad I made the decision to get a Keurig. Only a few minor flaws: wish it brewed a 12oz cup, and held more water. Besides that, mades a quick handy cup of coffee. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8890, 13, 2, 1, '2016-09-23', 'Not Sure why Everyone is Raving I bought this model a week ago, I\'ve owned larger Keurigs previously (loved them) but needed something compact.  So far I\'ve brewed 3 pods of coffee, one of cocoa, and one of chai latte all at the 8 oz setting.  Every single attempt gave a watered down, slightly hot beverage.  SO DISAPPOINTING -- unit is being returned.'),
(8891, 13, 2, 1, '2015-06-09', 'Slow, Pokey I\'ve describe above what I don\'t like'),
(8892, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-07', 'If nothing else The new Keurig replaced an older model I purchased about 5 yrs ago. I enjoy using the newer model because it has the. 4oz- strong option that the older model does not have. The coffee tastes better with the newer model.   I don\'t like that Keurig doesn\'t give you the vinegar - water cleaning option and they now have a \"filter\" that must be used and replaced when it\'s time.'),
(8893, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Great machine! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I love this machine. The size is great for small spaces. The coffee is excellent! Very quiet.'),
(8894, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-11', 'So great We are so happy with this! We\'ve had it just over a week but so far seems to be just perfect.'),
(8895, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-31', 'Perfect Keurig! This Keurig is great! It is easy to use and also extremely convenient. It is a little more compact than the other Keurig models which is something I strongly preferred. Although I do like all models, this is one of my favorites. I love its versatility in the different beverages that are available as well as the brands that the cups come in.'),
(8896, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Love it so far! I ordered this last Thursday, and got it today, Saturday. Easy to install/set up. Was surprised how fast it heats the water but wished it did a 12 oz instead of the low end 4 oz'),
(8897, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-27', 'Pretty color I\'ve been using it and I Love it so far. 8 oz coffee not enough for me though, but I have to follow the instructions on kpods'),
(8898, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-01', 'Love my new 2.0 This is my third Kuerig and I love it. I have always had the single serve models and this one with the refillable tank and size choices makes me so happy. Plus, having a filter means I don\'t have to waste money on bottled water.'),
(8899, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-21', 'Perfect Cup of Coffee I love this for making a quick cup of coffee. I really like how there\'s so many different k-cup brands and flavors so you can have a different cup of coffee every day. I have even made iced coffee with it and it worked great. It was really easy to set up with the instructions. One downside is that it is a bit loud, I have seen other Keurig machines that are much more quiet. It\'s not the worst thing ever but just a note. It seems like the water goes pretty quickly, maybe the tank isn\'t as large as some others that I\'ve used before but since I\'m usually only making one or two cups I don\'t actually have to fill it that often. I haven\'t tried to brew a carafe but it\'s great that is an option incase you wanted to make a pot of coffee. Overall a really great product that I would recommend to anyone.'),
(8900, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Love it!! Love my new coffee pot, and the color is awesome!!!'),
(8901, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-31', 'One of the best products I\'ve ever used! Before using this product I was only a casual coffee drinker. Now I can\'t get enough! The design of the machine is so simple, yet elegant and easy to use. They have such a wide variety of coffees, along with other drinks that you can never run out of flavors to try! This is absolutely worth buying 100 times over.'),
(8902, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-25', 'Returning our 3rd Machine! We have had 3 of these machines in our house. We have never gotten a decent cup of coffee out of any of them. The third machine never even brewed the first cup without stopping and saying the needle was clogged. Grounds all over our counter again. Wasted K-Cups and time. Keurig is now replacing with the 350. This better work or we will never have a Keurig in our house again. We resisted buying a Keurig as there was only one coffee drinker in our house. If the different model isn\'t any better. There will never be another Keurig in our house.'),
(8903, 13, 2, 4, '2016-09-29', 'so easy to use! Brought this one to replace my other one that was bigger but was not working as it should after only having for almost 2 years.  This model may be smaller but I love it! so easy to use and has features that my bigger model did not have.'),
(8904, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-12', 'Disappointed I received a Keurig coffee maker as a gift and was so excited to try it. After trying 10 times to make a cup of coffee, I called company to complain. They sent a new one free of charge, but had the same thing happen with the replacement. Very, very disappointed.'),
(8905, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Love it! I bought this keurig to replace my keurig mini. The oasis (mint) was my color choice & it\'s beautiful! A little deeper of a color than shown in the picture. It\'s touch screen which is nice! You can choose your brew size & strength! The only negative I can say is that I had to buy a new filter pod (for making your own coffee with grounds) for $14.99 because my old brewer\'s pod was incompatible. Overall, great purchase though & I\'m very happy with it!'),
(8906, 13, 2, 3, '2015-04-21', 'Quiet, but watch what packs you purchase Setting up my brewer wasn\'t as easy as I expected as I ran into an issue during it\'s initial setup - it took about 15 minutes and me turning the system off before it was ready. The instructions didn\'t exactly match the setup process that I noticed. I like how quiet the system seems to be, but there are two negatives I can think of: 1) I don\'t like how you have to use specific k-cup packs that teamed up with Keurig. As I try to transition to more organic coffees, I don\'t like being limited to what I can use. 2) For the price, I can\'t stand that it doesn\'t come with a carafe. And, of course, it supposedly only works with the Keurig Thermal Carafe for another $30 plus shipping. I love the convenience of Kuerig and there are many good basic brands of coffee available for the machine, but it\'s not as convenient as previous models in my opinion.'),
(8907, 13, 2, 1, '2016-06-12', 'Ugh! Only Brews Keurig Cups! I thought the new ones were supposed to brew any brand cups, but I keep getting an error message. This is going back to the store tomorrow and Keurig lost a customer!'),
(8908, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-19', 'Doesn\'t Work Have 350 model but this isn\'t listed anymore. Less than a yr after purchase it quit reading labels and began to reject Keurig brand k-cups. Called in & was told this was not possible and I was just not cleaning the machine properly. This was not first one I owned and it was being cleaned regularly and properly. Keurig wouldn\'t replace - instead sent a \"cleaning kit\" which was useless. Husband is furious that it requires putting K-cup in and out anywhere from 5 to 10 times before machine will read. Isn\'t worth the aggravation and wouldn\'t recommend to my worst enemy. It\'s a shame - we loved our original Keurig which gave out from constant use.'),
(8909, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'This thing rocks! I was anti keurig for years refusing to have to buy pods!! I finally caved because at night, or randomly during the day, I like just one cup of coffee and it\'s such a pain to do in a regular coffee pot.  So I watched this baby for a few months and then got the deal of the century - $89.99, extra 30% off and a $15 promotional gift card !  It is exactly what I was hoping for!!!  The coffee is great tasting, it\'s hot, I love the convenience for myself and when guests are over.  I still use my regular drip pot for mornings for the family, this is just \"supplemental!\"  The baby blue is my favorite color and it coordinates with blue and gray house colors.  Love it!'),
(8910, 13, 2, 3, '2015-08-24', 'Not all prior k cups work prior to purchase of the product You CANNOT use the prior K cups some not all will work the Company should let the consumer know.\'I receiced compensation/free product for my unbiased view\"'),
(8911, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-10', 'Easy to use I really like the sleek look this Keurig has with the water tank in back. It makes this work in a smaller area on counter and doesn\'t take up as much room. It also allows you to just use water and not have a cup in the holder, for use with hot chocolate, tea bags, ets.'),
(8912, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-23', 'PLASTIC TASTING COFFEE After purchasing my K200 on 1/23/16, my coffee continued to taste of hard plastic. I ran 2 full reservoirs of straight white vinegar followed by 4 reservoirs of fresh water. No improvement. Taking it back for refund tomorrow. No excuse for this problem to exist.'),
(8913, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-13', 'Love this brewer! This brewer works wonderfully! I\'m so glad that I decided to upgrade. The only thing that I\'ve found to be an issue would be getting an error message about using the wrong K-cup. We bought the Keurig reusable filters not the knock off brand and every once in a while we still get this error. We also get it a lot when there isn\'t a filter in it at all. We just open and close it to get the message to go away. Minor annoyance but overall still love this brewer!'),
(8914, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-07', 'Skeptic no more! Before I used this product, I was skeptical about the quality of a Keurig over other brands of single-serve pod-using coffee makers. I was using another brand before I received this Keurig, and let me tell you: I can taste the difference. This machine brews coffee that tastes smoother, less bitter, and (let\'s face it) better. I don\'t know if this is because of the pod-scanning technology, or if it\'s because the model is superior, but they\'re doing something right. The only thing that I don\'t like about this model is that you can\'t use non-Keurig certified pods, or the reusable pods. If you could, I\'d give the produce five stars!'),
(8915, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-20', 'Love it! I got the light blue color and it\'s so cute! It does look dirty because of splashback from the coffee, but can easily be wiped away. I also bought a reusable cup so I can use my own coffee. The coffee comes out hot, I love that you can make it strong as well. It doesn\'t take long to brew. This Keureg saves my life when I wake up late in the morning!'),
(8916, 14, 2, 4, '2015-02-03', 'So far, so good... After reading some sad reviews on this product, I decided to chance it anyways. This item seems to me, to be a \"love it\" or \"hate it\" product. For myself, the price was right, the blender is made of glass, and I was looking for a glass blender. The base isn\'t anything special, but it has a lot of different settings. I was a little bit disappointed when it came with only one blade, which is the blending/smoothie blade. But, I\'ve used it to blend some soup, so the blade is still versatile. I honestly believe that the problems I keep reading about (Won\'t crush ice; Motor blows), are being caused by people overloading it. My husband made some beautiful smoothies with this baby, yesterday... No problems with our blender still (thus far). And who knows... I could be wrong and this could just be a hit or miss product. Like I said, \"love it\" or \"hate it\". As for myself and my family, we \"like it\". It works for us and as long as it continues working, we\'ll continue liking it!'),
(8917, 14, 2, 4, '2014-11-29', 'The Black & Decker blender was purchased for myself, I purchased two more to give as gift, because one of two is always wanting to use mine. Get you own. Very user friendly, and I hadn\'t had any problems with mine. Never has my aunt or cousin. Purchased over 4 years agp.'),
(8918, 13, 2, 4, '2015-10-07', 'LOVE my new Keurig Absolutely love the convenience of this machine. Very easy to use once set up.'),
(8919, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-23', 'Great Customer Service I love my keurig and was so bummed when it wouldn\'t work. They sent me a new one and it\'s fantastic!'),
(8920, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-11', 'keurig 200 love the machine and new aqua color. the size is perfect for my kitchen'),
(8921, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-01', 'Love it This works great. I have one cup a day and it makes a smooth cup of coffee.'),
(8922, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-21', 'Buying this Keurig 2.0 K200 was a great decision I never thought I would buy a Keurig but was recently at a Bed & Breakfast that had one for the guests to use. I feel in love with the ease and convenience of the Keurig, came home and bought one a week later.'),
(8923, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-20', 'Excellent Brewer Water reserve is small. We love the machine but would have loved to have gotten a package deal with carafe and K cup holder. We received this from a third party to try and review. It\'s definitely getting a lot out of it and will continue using. It also does not have the cleaning issues older machines have had.'),
(8924, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-19', 'Love it! Love this machine!!!  Looks great, easy to use, versatile, economical, and makes hot drinks!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(8925, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-22', 'So simple This product is amazing! I use it daily and I have used tons of K-Cups as well as filling my own reusable K-cup. Its able to make iced coffee, iced tea, hot chocolate, even hot water in seconds! It is easy to use and I don\'t waste coffee anymore. I like the option to make a full pot when I have family/friends visiting. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I received compensation/free product for my unbiased review.'),
(8926, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-07', 'dont buy it ,waste of money. please donot waste money on this coffee brewed is not at all good, have to clean it frequently as stops working in between due to coffee grounds getting stuck in it.'),
(8927, 13, 2, 4, '2015-11-18', 'Doesn\'t brew hot enough This is my second review. I wrote the first one with the promise from Keurig that I would get free coffee. They denied receiving my review and would not send me my coffee. Aside from that, I am basically happy with my brewer. I do find that if you put cream in your coffee, the coffee is instantly too cold. I was told my the company to put hot water in the cup to warm it first to help with this issue. Over all, it is convenient and tastes great.'),
(8928, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-29', 'Love it! I absolutely love this product. I am beyond happy to own it. I had the regular keurig prior to this, but I love how this one has a variety of cup sizes. I also love the sleek look. I love all of the different types of drinks that I can make in this. I am saving so much money from using my Keurig rather than buying coffee every morning. I use this product before work and on the weekends!'),
(8929, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-10', 'Love my Keurig!! I purchased this Keurig because I was first introduced to the Keurig family during my internship, the machine make coffee \"making\" fun and simple. Pop in your favorite coffee pod and wait for no more than a minute and have a fresh, perfect cup of coffee prepared for you. I love my new K250 Keurig and the best part, it\'s in my favorite color!! As a college student a simple yet fun item is a must have in your dorm or even in your parent\'s kitchen when you\'re living at home. I cannot picture my life without my Keurig and I love that it makes K-Carafe sizes, my maker came with a free K-Carafe as an offer for purchasing it, and I couldn\'t be happier. I can\'t get enough about telling my friends and family members to purchase a Keurig, even if it\'s not this particular size, you can never go wrong with any Keurig you purchase! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8930, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-28', 'Dont work Save your money its not all its cracked up to be'),
(8931, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-20', 'Best Machine Yet This, in my opinion, is the best product that Keurig has come out with to date for simple coffee. It is small, fast and makes a great cup of coffee, tea, hot chocolate, etc. I would definitely recommend this anyone.'),
(8932, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Great quality. I first tried the k400 model which was great but just too big for only the two of us. So I recently purchased this model and it is the perfect size. Really quiet, and fast machine. Love it!'),
(8933, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-16', 'Luv it Love the color Serenity,  it\'s a lovely lavender blue.  The machine is easy to operate and it arrived very quickly .'),
(8934, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Can\'t go wrong with a Keurig! I bought this as a gift for my boyfriend for Christmas. He has thanked me multiple times and already used this countless times. Pros are that It takes a few minutes to make the coffee, we bought the k cup where you put the coffee grounds inside and it works great, it\'s easy to use and the  design is very nice. So far there aren\'t any cons!'),
(8935, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-30', 'my keurig I love the convenience of this product. All I have to do is get a very expensive keurig cup and I am ready to go. But like I said the cups are very expensive vs. the traditional coffee.'),
(8936, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-30', 'Makes the best cup of coffee! I use my Keurig every morning. It brews while I feed the cat. It\'s super fast and easy to use. I love that I can change up my coffee cravings daily w/o buying big tubs of coffee. And it comes out hot, even after I pour my creamer in it. I really look forward to my mornings now. My son loves it to make his hot cocoa or tea and he makes it now w/o all the mess. Thanks for a fabulous product. I have no negatives.'),
(8937, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-11', 'Cute and functional! This Keurig coffee maker is a great turquoise blue which gives a pop of color to my countertop and brightens my morning. It functions as good as it looks. It is super easy to use and makes hot coffee in seconds. It\'s so easy my 10-year old daughter set it up for me and taught me how to use it. I get my coffee quick and easy and my kids get their hot chocolate. It has made my mornings easier.'),
(8938, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-12', 'Love it! I got hooked on Keurig while visiting my sister and bought one as soon as I got home. I love the compact size of the K250 and have it nestled in a corner of the counter top. Great coffee selections and fast brew time for that quick cup on the way out the door. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8939, 13, 2, 4, '2015-12-18', 'Making carafe if coffee I have called the 866 number twice and received excellent help from customer service. The lady told me exactly what I was doing wrong and I easily corrected it per her instructions. Thank You!'),
(8940, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-30', 'Love my new brewer! This is my favorite brewer yet! It is quiet, stylish, and holds plenty of water for several cups, yet fits in a narrow space on our counter. Although it comes in several colors, we think the traditional black is the classiest look.'),
(8941, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-05', 'What a Treat Really enjoy using the Keurig and drinking the well-made coffees, etc.  It is a treat to be able to make just a cup whenever you want it, coffee, tea, hot chocolate.  What is great is that it will display a message if you need to refill the water or are using the wrong type of pod. We had a Mr. Coffee pod machine for a couple years and it cannot compare to the Keurig quality.-'),
(8942, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-22', 'I\'m very impressed! I like its flexibility to choose cup size as well as coffee strength. I particularly like the touch display control panel which clearly explains actions to take. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8943, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-27', '2.0 k350 Just bought this yesterday. K350 2.0. I hate it. Coffee is not hot, nor did it brew 10oz. This was the main reason I decided on this model. Very disappointing.'),
(8944, 13, 2, 4, '2015-12-19', 'no info on how to turn the machine off. this is quieter than my 4 year old Keurig. was a gift to my 96 year old mother she loves it. we just can not find a way to turn the machine off. that is bothersome.'),
(8945, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-30', 'New to the whole Keurig thing Got my Keurig 2.0 K250 as a gift and so far I like it and the many types of k-cups there are and will be trying. Only thing is how to power off? I did long press the power button on the screen and the screen just blacks out and the power button stays on so I guess that\'s it. Like how easy it is to use and will be telling my friends that are coffee drinkers that waste a whole pot about the Keurig 2.0'),
(8946, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-30', 'love it!!! i used to tell my husband i didn\'t need it, but now that i have i can\'t imagine not using it everyday to get my morning coffee! definitely recommend this one for easy use :)... thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8947, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-06', 'Love it I don\'t have much to say, just that we love that we found a light blue Keurig to match our aqua sky KitchenAid mixer! It\'s very easy to use and it is good for those who don\'t drink coffee every single day but want a fresh cup of really good coffee... or hot cocoa, or apple cider! Or if I want tea, I just dispense hot water.'),
(8948, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-22', 'Nice color The violet coffee  Keurig I ordered was just what I wanted. I have not used it yet but I will for Christmas. So I can not rate all the questions at this time.'),
(8949, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Keurig K2000 Coffee Maker Excellent Buy We had the smaller Keurig coffee maker. We wanted to upgrade to a larger size. What a deal! We bought it on a day coffee makers were 30% off. Plus we received a $15 Target gift card. Excellent coffee maker!'),
(8950, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Gotta have my coffee Love convenience especially on busy mornings when I have to leave early. Have the purple one and it is gorgeous!!'),
(8951, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-24', 'Convenience Love my Keurig 2.0 and Very easy to operate. Also, like the,support group at Keurig.com'),
(8952, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-13', 'My First Keurig Very easy to use. Makes beverage fairly quickly. Many choices of beverages. Can chose the size and strength of your drink. Fairly expensive, but worth it so far.'),
(8953, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-21', 'Extremely Dissatified Hard to clean. There is a tray in the cleaning area that needs to be cleaned every couple of cups.......otherwise liquid stays there and you cannot get a good cup of tea, hot chocolate, apple cider after a cup of coffee......Doesn\'t hold enough water. Unless the K Cup has a lavender or pink ring around it it will NOT work in this machine......makes no sense. I will be returning it to the store. We also purchased one for our office and will be returning it as well. I will/have shared my dissatisfaction with my family and friends and will continue to do so. Really disappointed in Keurig. I loved my old one........Unhappy in Texas.'),
(8954, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-18', 'Still deciding whether I like I replaced my older smile serve Kerrigan with this newer model. I wish now I had kept the older one. This does not fill the cup anywhere near what it says. I cannot use the many pics I already had,thus money gone.am disappointed there is no shut off,stays on at all times,and is very warm by day\'s end.(Have taken to unplugging). Having thrown the box it came in away,and info(dumb,but really thought would be as good as previous model) am stuck with it. Over all,while the color is very nice,is not what I had hoped for. More than likely will put this away,and go for another coffe maker.'),
(8955, 13, 2, 1, '2015-07-21', 'Frustrating product I had an older version of Keurig that I loved. I drink 4+ cups of coffee each day which makes using K-cups expensive and wasteful. I was extremely disappointed to realize that all new Keurigs only function with K-cups. Even so, I bought a new one when my old machine broke because I think Keurigs brew better tasting coffee than other brands. The machine broke 2 days later and I have to return it. I will be buying a different brand of machine. However, thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8956, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-29', 'Exceeded Expectations I bought this machine because I was looking for a fast way to brew coffee at home, without having to make an entire pot. My dad has a Mini Keurig that was purchased 6+ years ago that I\'ve always loved and has held up quite well. I\'m very glad I opted for the 2.0, as the Minis these days look and feel really cheap. The 2.0 is only $20 more, but exceeded my expectations in almost every way. The touch screen is much nicer than I expected, and I love the options it gives. I was pleasantly surprised that the non-Keurig brand of pods I have WORK in this machine. My only complaint is that this doesn\'t come with the My Kcup refillable pod.'),
(8957, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-04', 'Best purchase ever! I purchased this item during targets Christmas sale and paid next to nothing for it! I set it up within 5mins and made great coffee. I purchased the keurig Starbucks kcups and so far I haven\'t had any issues. Even my 8 year old uses it to make hot chocolate by herself. Very easy and convenient to use.'),
(8958, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-22', 'Great Product! Not only does this coffee machine make delicious coffee, but it also adds a stylish look to your kitchen. The quality of the product combined with the limitless varieties of coffee offers me a great cup of coffee. I would definitely recommend this machine to a friend.'),
(8959, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-13', 'We ADORE it! We absolutely LOVE our Keurig ,and the assortment of wonderful products that go along with it. Making coffee, tea, iced tea, etc, is a breeze. Since we started using our Keurig we have noticed we are drinking more iced beverages, which is what we would normally purchase a the coffee shop. Some people say the pods are expensive, but when you factor in the round trip drive to the coffee shop , plus the product we buy, we are definitely saving money using the Keurig. That being said, we do wish that you could use other brand Kcups as well. We have found a variety we would love to try, but aren\'t able to. I understand the reasoning behind Keurig making the machine this way, however, the ability to use a variety of k cup brands would make this even more valuable in our household. We do like that there is the ability to brew a carafe rather than a single cup, but don\'t like the fact that we have to purchase the carafe separately at the price of approx. $30. I would definitely recommend this to friends, and family as it\'s a great alternative to the coffee shop, there is a great selection and it\'s quicker than a traditional coffee maker.'),
(8960, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Great buy Great sale price for Keurig.'),
(8961, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-06', 'Fantastic brewer I love the ease with the 2.0 that was not offered with the older Keurigs. This one is easier to use and provides a better tasting cup of coffee than my previously owned Keurig. Excellent ease and fantastic cups of coffee. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8962, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-22', 'I love my new Keurig! I purchased in the Oasis color which is exclusive to Target and got a great deal with the Black Friday pricing + a $15 giftcard. Cannot beat that! The color is a beautiful mint and it looks perfect in my kitchen. I bought it to replace the mini which does not have a reservoir. It was super easy to set up and I have used it almost every day since, especially in this cold Colorado weather. If I have anything negative to say about it, it\'s that the shape of the machine is a little awkward. It seems like it would be more boxy, but it isn\'t. Not a deal breaker, but not quite as sleek in design as the classic. I have it sitting caddy-corner (sp?) and it compliments the Kitchen Aid mixer I have sitting on my counter. My beverages come out piping hot and I have the option to dispense hot water only. It will only work with Keurig branded K cups, but you can by the Keurig cheat specifically for this machine for a good price.'),
(8963, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-31', 'Great Machine And Don\'t Believe Some Of The Bad Reviews This is just a great product!. I have to laugh at some of the silly, negative reviews on this machine. Every problem that I read in the reviews has a simple solution. For instance, you can use a My K-Cup Filter and use whatever kind of coffee you want. Read several reviews saying how \"selfish\" Keurig is and how limited you are on how you can brew coffee. Just not true! Read that you can\'t brew 10 ounce cups with K-Cups. Again, not true. You can brew 4,6,8, and 10 ounce cups with K-Cups. As for old K-Cups people are complaining about, the only ones that don\'t work are K-Cups from 2014!! If you have K-Cups that old, it\'s time to throw them away anyway. This K200 can do anything that an old machine can do and do it so much better with much more freedom, ease, and variety. This is my second Keurig coffee maker. My first one was the Office Pro from 2011. Loved, loved, loved that machine. It still works great and gave it to a friend when I got my K200 2.0. The K200 makes so many improvements and is so much easier to clean as well. I love how quiet the new machine is and love the water filter too. Pick up any of the new 2.0 machines and you won\'t be disappointed. You\'ll get a good, cup, mug or carafe every time. Have some friends that have the K500 and they absolutely prefer there new machine from their old Keurig machine. Really wanted the K500 model as well but this K200 just fits my limited counter space so much better. I really love Keurig and can\'t even imagine going back to a regular coffee maker. So happy with my purchase and I hope that this K200 brings me the many, many, many days of great coffee and beverages like my Office Pro did for 5 years. Thank you Keurig!!!!'),
(8964, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-29', 'Error message with water pressure Thank you for your wonderful customer service !! !!'),
(8965, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-14', 'Absolutely Amazing!!! I use my Keurig multiple times a day and I absolutely love it. I love that is has a strong setting and a other setting for tea. Its easy to use and its very quick. I love that it keeps water preheated so its always ready when I want a cup of coffee. I don\'t know how I ever lived with out it and I don\'t know what I would do if i didn\'t have it now.'),
(8966, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-12', 'Gorgeous Color! this turquoise keurig will add a happy splash of color to home or office!'),
(8967, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-12', 'Great convenience for the beginning of my day You replaced my broken one \"still in warranty\" fast and courteous people.. thank you...'),
(8968, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-20', 'keurig works great I was looking for a keurig that wouldnt take too much counter space but also has options for various amounts, including the karafe feature. A big thing for me was that keurig would work with other brands of pods, my favorite coffee is camerons coffee and their pods do not use plastic, the keurig accepts the pods even though it is not their brand of pod. Works great and love how it quick it is to brew a cup of coffee in the morning. Also, love the feature of just getting hot water from it for my tea bags.'),
(8969, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Love it First of all, I ordered the oasis color because it matches my new kitchen aid perfectly!! I have had a cup of coffe every morning since I bought it! Super easy and quick. Would definitely recommend!'),
(8970, 13, 2, 5, '2016-04-27', 'We love it! We hesitated to get a Keurig for many years but finally decided when this one came out. Price was reasonable so we gave it a try and could not be happier. It fits nicely on our counter and under cupboards - it\'s not big and clunky like older models. We have it sitting near the sink so all we have to do is fill it with our sprayer - don\'t have to move the pot at all to refill the water. It heats up really fast and delivers a nice hot cup of coffee which is a requirement - no lukewarm java in our house. We are just really, really pleased. So much that we bought one for our daughter who was still using a mini - she is just as happy with hers.'),
(8971, 13, 2, 4, '2015-12-14', 'Happy purchass! Lovely little coffee machine. I purchased this model in store and received a $20 gc that I used toward a Carafe. Pros: great taste! Easy to use! Large options in flavored coffee! Easy clean up! Cons: Warm up slow. The filter set-up takes a bit of time. I never owned/used a Keurig before, so the brew number selection was confusing. Pricy pods. All in all I like it. These things I will just have to get used to. I purchased a reusable filter for the 2.0 model, which shoud save some money. To the people who are unable to use the older pods, dump the contents into 1 of those things??? Anyways, enjoy!!!'),
(8972, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Great fast coffee!!! We  purchased the turquoise for ourselves ( pearl was sold out) and oasis as a gift. Best purchase ever and they hit our doorstep in less than 3 days! Extremely happy with Target and Keurig.'),
(8973, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Great machine and cute! I\'ve owned many Keurigs in the past and ALL of them have turn out to break within 6 months, I\'m not sure what this one will do but the overall  Quality on this one alone seems much better than my last ones. I got the oasis color and it is so cute in my house. The coffee comes out really great I like my coffee strong so I hit the strong brew button, and my coffee tastes amazing. I  recommend this machine, and I\'m very happy with Keurig again!'),
(8974, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-18', 'Great cup of coffee I have had my new brewer for a few weeks now. I would say something bad about my brewer but I cant. I makes a really good cup of coffee. My girlfriend also says the tea K-cups are great as well.'),
(8975, 13, 2, 2, '2016-12-13', 'Disappointed I had an older model Keurig for years and it worked without issue. I thought I was missing out on something with these newer models so I purchased this one because I love the variety of colors available. Unfortunately, I\'m having the same water pressure issue I\'ve seen mentioned in other reviews. This has led to wasted K-cups and coffee grounds in my coffee. I thought there might be trouble when I opened the box and saw the Brewer Maintenance Accessory. It was a total red flag that indicated there was likely an ongoing problem with the brewers that Keurig is aware of. This also probably explains why it was on sale and included a gift card with purchase. I\'m very disappointed. I recommended this to a friend as a Christmas gift for her husband and will be letting her know that would be a mistake.'),
(8976, 14, 2, 1, '2015-08-20', 'Ridiculous I bought this blender since our last blender (a Cuisinart) broke after 3 years. I thought Black and Decker was a good brand, so I got this one. I\'m making a smoothie and about 20 seconds into blending it starts to slow down. The power is terrible. About 2/3 of the way done and the thing completely stops because it over heated. It never came back on either. Tried it again an hour later after it cooled and still absolutely nothing. Didn\'t get my smoothie either. Was too chunky. Such a waste of money and going straight back to B&D. Moving on up to an Oster'),
(8977, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-23', '\"Some girls just wanna have fun, I just wanna have Coffee!\" So, I love coffee, maybe a little to much. I have wanted a Keurig for some time now and Have finally got my hands on one! Yayyy me! (It was my birthday, umm, my 25th one. That will be my only lie in this review, promise!) My son has decided to send me to coffee rehab. I have had a Mr.Coffee KCup brewer for a while and it has worked beautifully and makes a great cup of coffee, but what can I say, Its like driving a nice car but you dream of a cadillac. Anyway, I purchased the \"Strawberry\" colored Keurig 2.0 200 today. It was a hard choice between it and the blue, both are beautiful. So, out with Mr.Coffee and in with Mrs.Keurig :) I have made around 4 cups of coffee today and have been impressed so far. Hopefully I will not be let down. For me this was a pricey purchase. (I\'m not poor, but I\'m not rolling around in the dough either) I have to budget what I do, but I feel this product so far is worth what I have invested. Fingers crossed that I can come back to this site in a year and still rave about this Gorgeous Machine that has taken over my life. Thanks Keurig! :)'),
(8978, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-18', 'My goal is to create a life I don\'t need a vacation from. I have my Keurig on a small cart in our bedroom and can brew a cup of coffee first thing in the morning while getting ready for work. Makes a cup fast when I am in a hurry.'),
(8979, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-26', 'Love it now, hate it later Like so many other Keurigs, mine worked for a few months, then started only pumping a fraction of a cup. Did all the usual things that customer service suggests...ran cleaner through it multiple times, cleaned the needle (which wasn\'t plugged), etc. It finally stopped working altogether. Called Keurig and was told they would send me a new brewer...at a small discount. No thanks. The problem with a Keurig is the pump. It malfunctions. So for all those who post reviews like \"I love it!\", come back in a few months and let us know if you still love it. That\'s the problem with most reviewers. they don\'t wait and see how long the product lasts.'),
(8980, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-03', 'Sadly Dissatisfied We use a Keurig primarily for when just one person is going to have a cup or when we have company over and we want to offer both caffeinated or decaffeinated. Our old Keurig broke and so we decided to venture into the world of 2.0. We ordered this one in orange (to my wife\'s joy), and within a week, it was giving us significant grounds in the coffee. We called customer support, went through some tests, and then they sent us new one. We received the new one and within the first or second brew, we had grounds! We went through tests again and to no avail. We asked customer support to send us a different and upgraded Keurig - which they did, and we are within a week of that one. So far, so great. That said, there must be some type of defect with this type of Keurig. I can\'t imagine we received the two totally odd ones in a batch.'),
(8981, 13, 2, 4, '2015-11-27', 'all most perfect I would recommend this machine to my friends after explaining my concerns to them. Over all I enjoy the machine and all the features it includes. It does make my pod shopping a little more challenging.'),
(8982, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-16', 'GREAT Investment I received my new Keurig a few weeks ago. I purchased the teal one and it is even more beautiful in person! I\'ve made several types of coffees and teas and none have disappointed. It makes the perfect amount of drink and doesn\'t take up too much space on my counter. The maintenance is also very easy. I would highly recommend this product.  P.S. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8983, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Great for the perfect cup of coffee! I recently switched from the basic Keurig to a Keurig 2.0 and I was surprised by how different the two are! The 2.0 was a bit complicated to figure out at first but I would definitely recommend this one! I use my Keurig daily, before work and in the morning on the weekend. It\'s quick and easy and each cup is brewed to perfection. I never have to worry about making a cup too strong or weak. I also love that there is an option to brew loose leaf tea. The possibilities are truly endless.'),
(8984, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Happy coffee lovers Love this new Keurig and love the new turquoise color! The touch screen is easy to use and the coffee seems to brew a little faster than my last Keurig. It is nice being able to choose what size cup we want to brew as well as how strong the coffee is. I think we will enjoy being able to make a carafe of coffee when friends and family drop by too. We have yet to be disappointed by one of your brewers. Lets hope this one lasts as long as the last one did! Thank you Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(8985, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-09', 'Awesome! We use this machine daily. So simple! Kids love they can make their lemonade, tea, or hot chocolate by themselves. This has become the appliance we can\'t live without. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(8986, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-24', 'my first Keurig this is the first time ive owned a keurig. i drink a lot of coffee, so i always made it by the pot. this is much faster though, which works well when im short on time.'),
(8987, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-03', 'Miss the Mini The sleek style of this Keurig is very appealing. I am a frequent coffee drinker, and have no desire to use any other brand of coffee other than Keurig brands (the kcup offers all I want, while larger size cups are extremely limited). My issue is that I like to brew more than 10oz with one Kcup. The 2.0 K200 brewer I recently purchased limits the amount you can brew without changing to a different pod, and therefor, it doesn\'t suit my taste like the single-serve mini that I previously used for the past 2 yrs. Even after cleaning and running water through several times, I get a plastic taste on top of the limited ounces. If I can\'t get this resolved, I won\'t be using this system anymore.'),
(8988, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-04', 'Very happy with this machine This is the first Keurig machine that I\'ve owned and I have to say the whole experience has been really good. I use this machine at work in my office five days a week. The coffee has been great tasting and brews very quickly. My only complaint would be that even on the 10oz. size, it doesn\'t fill my cup completely. I know I can buy the larger K-mug sizes, but I was just a bit disappointed that I would need to to fill my cup to the top. That being said, I really like how easy the whole operation is. The main reason I bought this machine was to get away from all the cleaning I had to go through with a normal drip machine. Measuring the coffee, dealing with the grounds, it was just a big pain. The 250 works just like I expected it to. Thinking of getting another one for my wife and I to have at home. Also, I\'ve noticed a quite a few people complain about having to buy the sanctioned K-Cups for the 2.0 machines. My local stores all seem to carry a really good assortment of the correct pods. In fact, I haven\'t seen any for sale that are not the correctly marked variety. Anyway, there are tons to choose from and I\'ve tried about six different ones.'),
(8989, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-26', 'Terrible product larger units work much better'),
(8990, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-06', 'easy to use keurig love this keurig, purchased as a gift for my mom. she is easily able to prepare her own coffee with a simple push of a button!'),
(8991, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Tom G loves his keurig Best cup of coffee ever!'),
(8992, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-23', 'so far so good. makes good coffee but it should have the karake included with the purchase price.'),
(8993, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'Wonderful Brewer This is my first Keurig and I absolutely love it. It is a wonderful size, does not take much space. Theres nothing better than having a very stylish appliance in your kitchen, it sure takes your kitchen into a modern realm. The option to make your coffee strong is absolutely amazing, I make sure to use it every time. It\'s also very easy to clean and maintain. It truly is a wonderful investment! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(8994, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-23', 'Love! Set up was super easy, and using it is as well. I love the sleek new design and digital display! Target had the best price around!'),
(8995, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-12', 'Office Work Horse! I brought this in for my office to use and abuse. We had the Keurig Elite K45 prior too, but the option to do a carafe of coffee was too perfect for us. Grabbed a carafe from a big box store and started to enjoy hot fresh coffee that stayed hot for HOURS. I am not kidding. In the carafe it was at least 4 hours of hot coffee. Too cool! In comparison to the Elite model, this one was definitely lacking in cup sizes, and for the tea drinkers in the office, the 4 oz or 6oz sizes were just too puny in comparison to the coffee sizes you can get from the machine. Sometimes I think it is almost too smart! I have yet to encounter the dreaded Opps! message, but I really do miss being able to use my own coffee in the reusable pods. I really hope that they come out with a compatible pod for that soon! Love how slim it is, and the touch screen. So far it is a great work horse and I am glad to have it!'),
(8996, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-18', 'I llove my new Keurig I start each morning with a cup of hot chocolate. It is so easy and quick to prepare. No mess to clean up. The purple color is elegant.'),
(8997, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Outstanding quality and easy to use Extremely convenient for my first 2 cups of coffee in the morning.'),
(8998, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-10', 'Good Coffee Stuff Color is great, I\'m. Long term Keurig consumer on my second model.  Love the sleek design of this model.  Only tiny problem is the noise factor when brewing.'),
(8999, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-26', 'Great coffee, but not useful for my travels First this makes great, fast coffee. I bought this unit to take with us when we travel (by car) on short and long holidays. The coffee units provided in condos or hotels is always so bad, that it seemed like a great idea to just carry this and have great coffee. The problem is that you cannot totally eliminate all of the water out of the unit. It holds water somewhere inside and there is not a drain available. So to use it for traveling and have that water sitting there between trips did not seem like a good idea. Sadly took it back and Target credited without a problem.'),
(9000, 14, 2, 2, '2014-07-23', 'meh.... liquify button does not liquify - my Hamilton Beach personal size blender did better..... but I needed bigger quantity......'),
(9001, 13, 2, 3, '2015-08-18', 'would be great if not for DRM This purchase was my first time owning a Keurig. I was impressed with the ease of use and the touch screen. Not impressed with the fact that I can only use certain pods and even those don\'t always read correctly. Also want impressed that this can\'t with no accessories. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(9002, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-18', 'Love it I love my Keurig brewer! I like that this brewer is compact and that I can brew all my favorite varieties!'),
(9003, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-12', 'awesome new Keurig I absolutely love the K250 Keurig Brewer that I got to preview for free from @Influenster. I previously had the Keurig Elite model, and although I liekd that one, I love this one more. I have very limited counter space and with the water resevoir wrapping around the back of the brewer, it frees up more space and looks much sleeker. I also love the additional size options, including brewing 4 cups at once with the carafe (which I wish came with this model, but I know I can always buy it seperatleyif I wish). The only thing I am disappointed by is that it does not take all Kcups. Some companies are starting to design the cups with filters attached, unlike the plastic cups that most brands use....I received an error message when trying to use the new style of cup. This has become my everyday brewer and just love Keurig!!'),
(9004, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-06', 'The Best I had the one cup brewer for the longest time. I recently upgraded myself to the 2.0. It\'s the best choice I\'ve made in years.'),
(9005, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'Great system Love my new Keurig 2.0. When researching I found the website confusing as it states that the system comes with the carafe, but in fact it does not. I have had several telephone conversations with both customer service and the corporate office, but the website has not been corrected yet. Buyer beware because if you are expecting to get a carafe and that is one of the reasons you are making this purchase, you will be disappointed. Other than that the system makes a great cup of coffee.'),
(9006, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-25', 'Love 2.0 Everyone in my household really likes this brewer, and they can all figure it out themselves. totally happy with this purchase'),
(9007, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-11', 'Worth the purchase I really enjoy using my Keurig 2.0, but I would have loved if Keurig made this mahine with the idea in mnd that we would like to continue using alternate or reusable cups as they DO NOT work with this machine. But I love it otherwise and am happy with my purchase!'),
(9008, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-05', 'In LOVE! I bought this for myself during a Black Fridays sale and I am IN LOVE with this machine! I am the only coffee drinker in our house so it super convenient for me. I love the variety of options in pods. The ease of use it also very nice as my 7 year old loves to use it for the hot water option for her oatmeal in the morning. The only downside is the brew size only goes to 10oz so I have to brew twice for my travel mug and if you were wanting to buy off brand pods they will not work with this machine, they have to be keurig branded.'),
(9009, 13, 2, 5, '2016-01-30', 'You can purchase \"My K Cup 2.0 filter\" to brew your own coffee in The K 200. I purchased the Keurig 2.0 after the iCoffee machine I purchased went kaput after less than a month. So far I am very happy with this machine and like that I can use my own coffee in the 2.0 my cup filter I purchased separately. Got it on sale at Target and received a $20 gift, too'),
(9010, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Amazing This is my new favorite item I own!!!! Love how easy it is!!!'),
(9011, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Great buy! Got this for a really great price after all discounts paid around $50. Cleaned it and plugged it up.. ready to go. Easy to use great design love it. Makes a quality brew!'),
(9012, 13, 2, 2, '2016-01-31', 'not much easier than brewed coffee I have to use that bulb that cleans the pin a couple times during the week. Finding brewed coffee might be less than a hassle!'),
(9013, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-27', 'This is pretty amazing! I love this product! The style is amazing and it is super easy to make a drink! It\'s really fast and easy to clean as well. I use it right before work almost everyday. My favorite drinks to make are the brew over ice options, they are great! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9014, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-27', 'Oasis Purchased the oasis color and it is GORGEOUS! So happy with this purchase and love it! Super easy to use and clean.'),
(9015, 14, 2, 5, '2015-12-08', 'Love the prices and easy to use Easy to install great blender'),
(9016, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-16', 'Love the new color! I saw this in the ocean color and had to have it. I found it on sale so it was a no brainer. Love that it has the 10 oz capability.'),
(9017, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-26', 'wonderful ease I got this machine for Christmas, it looked so complicated  coming out of the box. My husband came to help and how wonderful it is. Pressing a few taps on the screen, after filling the water, and hot coffee in the cup I choose and it\'s done! I love it.  No more half pots to pour down the drain because I wanted a fresh brewed cup.'),
(9018, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-12', 'What an Improvement over previous models!!! I\'m a coffeeholic and I love my coffee fresh! Keurig K-Cup system is wonderful for me!'),
(9019, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-15', 'I LOVE my Keurig and i LOVE the oasis color! Plus Target\'s customer service is a gold standard! So impressed with them. I had an issue with my order and they fixed it up A.S.A.P. no problem. :D'),
(9020, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'Coffee Love it. Easy to use!'),
(9021, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-27', 'Exactly what I wanted Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review. I have never had a Keurig or similar brewing system before this item. I needed a quick and easy way to make coffee before classes (I\'m in college) and this seemed to fit the bill pretty well. I knew several people who have Keurigs and they all seemed to like them so I went ahead and purchased one. Overall, I am very pleased with my purchase. The Keurig does exactly what it was advertised to do, but unfortunately this model does have a few drawbacks. I find that when going above 8 ounces or so, the coffee tends to taste weaker, which is just a drawback of the system I guess. Also, because of this, there is no option to make 12 or 14 ounces for travel mugs, which I found disappointing. Finally, the new 2.0 models of Keurig requires you to use the Keurig brand cups, which is kind of annoying. This is not too much of a drawback for me, however, because I planned on using the disposable cups anyway. If you are looking for a quick and easy way to make a cup of coffee, this if for you. If you want to use your own coffee or make more than a cup, you may need to look elsewhere.'),
(9022, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Love my new Keurig 2.0, long thorough review here! This is my 3rd Keurig machine. I\'ve gotten 3+ years life out of my last 2 and I put a lot of coffee through them! When my last one wasn\'t able to be fixed and the warranty had expired, I was excited that I could pick a new one. I immediately loved that the 2.0 was in color! I also was interested in the mini Keurig but decided on this one as I found the mini to be too small and I was able to get a deal with this machine that made it the same price as the mini. I purchased the turquoise and I love the color. It\'s just as bright IRL as it is in the stock photo online. I did notice that the Keurig 2.0 is also just slightly taller than my previous Keurig which works fine with it opening under my cabinet. Setup was very easy and my machine was ready to make coffee quickly! This machine comes with a charcoal filter you install and I brewed a few cups of hot water to clear any reside left from that. This machine also allows you to choose the strength at which you can brew...which I love! I have not tried brewing a carafe pod yet as I am the only coffee drinker in my house and have yet to entertain. I am excited for that option however! Finally, the only tricky part with this machine is that you are only allowed to brew Keurig certified pods in it. You cannot use store brands or the reusable filters with your own coffee. I have found a hack online for that which works if you want to take the time to do that but I\'m happy to use Keurig certified as they taste the best. Don\'t let that worry you, I think there are over 750 different pods available that work and most likely you won\'t have a problem. However, If the reusable filter is your go to, then you won\'t want this machine. Finally, make sure to register your Keurig online as you can get yours replaced within a year if something happens and also some deals on pods. I take my coffee seriously and did a lot of research before purchasing this one. I am very happy with my new machine and the fun color makes my morning routine a little brighter. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9023, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Best keurig yet! So easy to start using. Other brand k cup brewers tend to water down my coffee but with smart brewing technology, this makes the perfect cup. I also don\'t mind buying only keurig brand k cups.  Thanks keurig, for the free pods with this review!'),
(9024, 13, 2, 1, '2016-09-15', 'Sometimes it works I got this as a gift, I was super excited but every month I spend one week trying to figure out why it says that the water is under pressure and it won\'t work. I done everything in the book but nothings gets solved. I talked to customer service and same. When it brews it\'s great, the coffee is good it\'s just very frustrating!'),
(9025, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Great Brewer Great unit, i use this for my RV and it is a space saving over my original Keurig. Makes coffee quick with the same quality as original brewer. New colors are trendy. And, Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9026, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-07', 'Pleased I purchased the Keurig 250 2.0 as a gift for my husband. He really likes the convenience of it over our old drip coffee maker; getting a fresh cup of coffee each time as opposed to warming up a cup in the microwave to finish off a pot the next day. The only drawbacks that I notice is that the water reservoir is kind of small and needs to be filled after 3 10oz. cups of coffee and on occasion it doesn\'t make a full cup. I like the option to make a 4 cup pot with the carafe when we have company. Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9027, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-13', 'Simply love it! At first, I had to get used to the Keurig 2.0. I bought the wrong kind of k-cups at first, and could not use them in new Keurig. Other than that, I love it, and there are good deals on Keurig k-cups on this website.'),
(9028, 13, 2, 2, '2015-09-10', 'CAN NOT BREW A REFILLABLE CUP Everyone always brags that they have a Keurig, so I had a Black and Decker that did not like to brew the same size cup each time I used it. SO I finally went and bought a new Keurig. I AM UPSET that I can not brew my own coffee in an aftermarket pod where I add coffee to it like I could with my last one. I like being able to do this for one it is way cheaper. SO does Keurig only care about sales and NOT the customer. If they do not change this and make an adapter to let me do this, then I will look for a replacement so I can use my own coffee. I can not believe that I can\'t and I am very upset about this But no one from Keurig will see this and based on them not letting me brew my own coffee I can only assume they don\'t care.'),
(9029, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'First time Keurig user,not disappointed at all I had previously been reluctant to purchase a Keurig. I like to grind my own coffee and use the reusable kcups vs. Having to use the premeasured cups. Kids and wife use kcups. Found this to be quite enjoyable for all.'),
(9030, 13, 2, 2, '2016-02-12', 'Held hostage to Keurig brand k-cups! I\'ve owned A Keurig coffee maker for several years now. I decided to buy the K200 and found out Keurig has now added a sensor that will only allow it to use the Keurig brand k-cups. I refuse to let a coffee maker tell me what kind of coffee I have to buy since I don\'t always use their brand. I returned the coffee maker. Keurig will tell you it\'s done to give you the best brew. I think it\'s just to force you to buy their product. Keurig needs to rethink this latest \"innovation\". Guess I\'ll buy a Mr Coffee brand next that accepts the k-cups.'),
(9031, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Beautiful  Keurig This Keurig is so easy to operate I love it .Very excited to get up in the morning to have my coffee and use my Keurig and my different kinds of coffee . I just love it so  much I bought the Keurig 2.0 200'),
(9032, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Great deal, pleasure to use. I ordered online during a great promotion.  Received within 2 days I ordered online.  Already had a machine in white that was a year old.  This was such a good deal, I ordered in the teal color that I had been wanting.'),
(9033, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-28', 'Bought this as a present. Got this a Christmas present.  Her eyes lit up when she saw it was a Keurig.  She liked the idea that it could make either a cup or a pot full (pot was extra, but worth it).  She also liked that she could use it for different flavored coffees and hot chocolate.  Don\'t know how easy it is to clean as that is up to her.'),
(9034, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-27', 'Very versatile! I resisted getting a Keurig for some time as I was not sure how cost effective it would be (I can drink a LOT of coffee). With the new carafe size pods I decided to give it a try as my old coffee maker was no longer working properly. I really like all the beverage options and how fast it brews. My grandchildren love the juice, lemonade and hot cocoa kcups. The only thing I would change is having a bigger water reservoir such as the more expensive machines have. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9035, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-30', 'Love My Keurig K250!!! I just upgraded my Keurig from the old mini. The K250 was very easy to setup and use right out of the box. I did not realized there was a water reservoir. Love this new feature! I did not get the bigger ones because of space on my countertop. The K250 fits perfectly and looks very stylish in my modern kitchen.'),
(9036, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-03', 'I would buy this product again The taste is what coffee is suppose to taste like from a fast brewing machine. This one machine is perfect in the evening when you just want one cup of decaffeinated before bed.'),
(9037, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-09', 'My coffee maker Love it and the color'),
(9038, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-22', 'Love our keurig! We love our new keurig 2.0. The coffee it always hot and doesn\'t take much time to preheat. It is very simple to use and the different cup sizes are also a plus. My husband uses the strong coffee setting and he says that it is very good and never tastes burnt. I have not had one issue so far with our keurig and I don\'t have any issues with it at all.'),
(9039, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-16', 'review keurig at work heats quick, cant use pods without insignia'),
(9040, 13, 2, 4, '2015-11-19', 'Happy with our 2.0 so far I am happy with this new product because though it seems to plug up more often from coffee grounds it has been very easy to clean compared to the older model. It is a very convenient system we all know that, makes a good cup of coffee and allow you to vary the strength. My frustration with the older model was getting clogged up and slow brewing. My new 2.0 suddenly stopped brewing one day and support walked me through cleaning it with the included cleaning tool. What a difference it was back brewing like the first day. So I need to do this monthly but if that is all I have to do and it keeps on brewing like it does its a small price to pay. So far a much improved model compared to the first one. The screen is easy to use to make your size and strength selection and the big flashing button to brew couldn\'t be easier. Quick and easy clean up and have not run into any issues with odd brands not working. If find some brands are not maybe up to the same standards as others. I like 8 o\'clock Italian Roast but the foil top gets rips and enlarged during use and causes grounds to plug up the works (ergo the cleaning) but since I switched to another brand I don\'t have that problem. We just ordered a K350 to replace the old B45 in the kitchen.'),
(9041, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-24', 'This product is awesome! I really enjoy using my Keurig to make coffee and teas! This product was most defiantly worth the purchase! My keurig is stress free to use and does a phenomenal job curing my coffee obsession. I recommand you investing in this awesome product!');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(9042, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-03', 'poor product So far I have had it replaced x2. The first 2 had the same problem that they heated and dispensed hot water without pushing anything then just turned off, never to run again. 3rd one on the way so hopefully this will work longer than 3 months. we don\'t use it that often, not even daily and keep it turned off since the 1st one heated on its on so not sure if this is a defect or not. Would not buy for myself, was a gift.'),
(9043, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-30', 'Great Brewer I love this brewer. The touch screen is very intuitive and easy to understand, also, it includes a lot of extra settings like a checkbox for the desired strength of coffee and a hot cocoa setting. The lower tray is removable to accommodate for larger cups. My favorite thing to do is grab a large cup, fill it with ice, and brew an iced coffee k-cup to have a cool, refreshing drink. The only complaint I have is that it is a little bit noisier than the previous Keurig brewer, but it is worth it for the extra features.'),
(9044, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-20', 'Great! I use this machine almost daily. It is pretty simple to use, except sometimes the water reservoir is tricky. When I first got it I had to fill and refill the reservoir three times before it would register that the tank was full enough to brew a cup of coffee. I also like to drink hot tea and the cup size options for just hot water are not large enough. There is no 10oz option for hot water, which is what I prefer for my tea. So I end up having to brew hot water twice to get enough water. Overall, the machine is nice and basically like any other keurig. I have not, however, purchased the carafe, as it is quite a bit extra.'),
(9045, 13, 2, 2, '2016-04-14', 'Inconsistent Operation I never know if I\'ll actually get a cup of coffee out of my Keurig K-200. Sometimes it works great, recently it\'s very tempremental. I\'ve had it for just over a year, so I would think it should not be failing so soon.'),
(9046, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-18', 'LOVE I used to buy Starbucks every day which got expensive. My mom bought me my Keurig for nursing school and I have never been happier. It brews super fast and has so many different options. Super easy to use and so worth every penny. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9047, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-07', 'AMAZING Great product! Would highly recommend :)'),
(9048, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-28', 'K250 This is a very nice coffee maker for a single person like me. I brew a cup each morning and its fast and its fresh.'),
(9049, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Love it! I purchased this Keurig off of the website, and they delivered it fast! The set up was very easy. I like that a cleaning tool was included to clean the coffee grounds out as well.'),
(9050, 13, 2, 3, '2015-04-14', 'Just wish it was a little hotter! Although I have access to a Keurig at work, this is the first one that I\'ve owned in my home. I enjoy how quick it is to brew a cup of coffee, especially since a full pot would be too much for one person. The display is very easy to use and intuitive. My one complaint is that there isn\'t an option to adjust the beverage temperature. For some reason, the Keurig at my office brews hotter than this model. I personally prefer my beverages on the hotter side. I enjoy the variety of K-cups that are available, but I wish that previous versions were compatible with the 2.0 systems.'),
(9051, 13, 2, 2, '2016-02-07', 'Limited to only Keurig licensed k cups This replaced a Keurig that lasted just over 2 years and had only had bottled water in the tank. Absolutely hate my new one as it won\'t take the K cups that I\'d come to love. All the sample brands are too strong. Would never buy another Keurig knowing they shaft you into buying the more expensive k cups just to use their machine. May as well use my Mr. Coffee that brews by the pot, cost less than $15 and is over 5 years old.'),
(9052, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-17', 'So Far, So Good! We purchased this new Keurig 2.0 to replace our older model Keurig that was over four years old! We did have some concerns about it and had read very mixed reviews, but our old brewer was on its last leg and needed to be replaced. I wish the water tank was a little larger, but I love the size and compactness of this brewer which is why we chose it over the larger model. Sometimes it seems to take a long time to complete the brew cycle (keeps dripping for what seems like forever!) but overall, we\'re very pleased. Thanks, Kuerig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9053, 13, 2, 1, '2016-06-19', 'Disappointed Only makes appx 6 cups before needle maintenance is required. NM often takes up to 5 times to perform before regular coffee can be dispensed again. Total waste of money to purchase this Keurig.'),
(9054, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-19', 'Happy Bought this Keurig in red for my daughter as a Christmas giff! The girl  is ecstatic!! I lobe mine too'),
(9055, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-11', 'Replaced the first one and it doesn\'t work either. We bought the Keurig 2.0 and were so excited to use it. We got two in one day, both having the same problems. Here\'s our issue: 1. Leaves a lot of coffee grounds in the coffee. I had read that the needle is puncturing the K-cup filter. Poor design. This was the biggest issue because it\'s undrinkable. 2. Sometimes it makes the right amount, but most of the time it\'s way off. We brew 10 ounces and only get 4-6 back. 3. It ONLY uses Keurig brand coffee. Which isn\'t a major problem but a little annoying if we want to try other brands. 4. It brews hot, but not hot enough. Coffee makers are supposed to brew hotter than the consumer can stand to allow for adequate cooling, and allows for adding of refrigerated creamers. So what happens is my coffee now gets cold very fast. Previous Keurig\'s we\'ve owned did not have this problem. 5. We have had it one day and it no longer dispenses coffee. The screen continues to read \"error\" even though we have done everything by the book. Will be returning for a previous model. To add a positive note, I loved the option to make the coffee stronger, and it did exactly that! Disappointed in this model, but looking forward to Keurig hopefully making a better version.'),
(9056, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-07', 'Love it This is my 2nd Keurig and I love how sophisticated it is. If you don\'t want to use a kcup and just need hot water for your tea it will ask you if you want to dispense hot water only. Awesome! With my other Keurig you had to put a fake kcup in to get just water otherwise the water would splash all over. Also the touch screen is sweet - selecting desired size with your finger and it even asks you if you want your coffee strong. There is also a cocoa option. I have the turquoise color and love it. They had a light mint color in the store that wasn\'t available online that I might\'ve liked better, but it was too much hassle to exchange it on the spot at the store.'),
(9057, 14, 2, 1, '2015-12-13', 'Bad and cheap I bought it online and Since I pick it up the box was cheap. I come home and open it and saw the blender so cheap so I returned it'),
(9058, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Wonderful Viewer I love this Keurig! I used to own a Keurig mini, and while it could get the (limited) job done, it was severely lacking in size diversity, variety of beverages, ease of use, etc (I hated having to add water every time instead of having a reservoir). Before heading back to college this fall I decided to take the plunge and upgrade to the K250. It is everything I hoped for and more. The touch screen is easy to use, the reservoir is way sleeker than older models (My parents own the original Keurig), and the variety of beverages and sizes (from ~4oz to a whole carafe) is lovely. I\'ll definitely enjoy using this for a long time to come. It\'ll make my hectic college mornings easier to navigate since I\'ll have my own cup of coffee before even leaving my dorm! Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9059, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-13', 'Love This Machine! I love that this allows me to make different drinks for the members of our home as well as the option of a whole carafe (sold separately though I wish I was included - main con). My son and I both enjoy the fact that he can quickly and safely make his own hot cocoa.'),
(9060, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Love it I got this for Christmas and I love it.. very easy to use and I just love the color'),
(9061, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-31', 'Review I always used to think that keurig\'s were overrated and that they just did the same thing a regular coffee pot, guess I just didn\'t see the appeal. Then I got one for a gift and fell in love! It is great for the weekends when I want a fancy flavor and don\'t want a whole pot. Would definitely recommend this to friends in the future. Thanks, keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9062, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-20', 'Excellent Product This is a great product and works flawlessly!'),
(9063, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Quick and Easy I have never been much of a coffee drinker mainly because I didn\'t care to make a full pot of coffee in a traditional coffee maker. I have never had a Keurig before so I can\'t compare it to other models but I love this machine. I drink 90% more coffee now because of how easy and quick it is to make a cup whenever I want. I wasn\'t sure what to expect when I started to brew my first cup but I was so impressed. It was easy to set up for the first time and I love the way it looks. It is a good size and looks nice sitting on my kitchen counter. One complaint I have heard is that it would be better if you could use the reusable cup like in other Keurig models. I can imagine that would be helpful for people who drink a lot of coffee as the K-cups can get expensive. I, on the other hand do not drink enough coffee for it to be that big of a problem. I would definitely recommend this to anyone who wants an occasional cup of coffee.'),
(9064, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'I Love it!!! I am a first time Keurig owner and I have to say I\'m loving every moment of it. Life is just more fun and easier when you have a keurig. My most absolute favorite thing is that it comes in my favorite color even better. If you don\'t own one get one.'),
(9065, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'Perfect for College Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review! I really like that this comes in bright colors and that it has a water reservoir! This is a great brewer for the casual-everyday coffee drinker.'),
(9066, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-10', 'Excellent Brewer! I loved this new brewer. I use it at least twice in the morning (everyday), and more throughout the day on the weekends. I am impressed with the variety of cup sizes it brews, and the reservoir is big enough that I\'m not constantly refilling it. I also really love the slimmer design of the K200. It looks and fits wonderfully on my counter top!'),
(9067, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-23', 'Oasis is beautiful!! I loved this machine so much that I bought another one so I could have it at work and at home. The Oasis color is gorgeous, and I just realized that it\'s a special edition only sold at Target. Despite the electronic system being very particular about how much water in the machine or it won\'t work, it\'s very easy and fun to use. I appreciate the charcoal water filter because clean water makes coffee taste better. Definitely get this!'),
(9068, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-07', 'Keurig has done it again! My Keurig 2.0 works like a charm. Love the color (orange)! This is a great addition to my home. When setting up my Keurig I had a few questions and those questions were easily answered by the friendly representatives of Keurig. Now we are rolling with a cup or 2 each morning! Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(9069, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-29', 'Love My New Brewer I\'ve had previous Keurig Brewers and this by far is the best, love that I can chose strength, size and brew a pot of coffee if I chose. Down side is I can\'t brew my Tim Hortons kcups since they are not a recognized brand.'),
(9070, 14, 2, 1, '2014-12-31', 'Used it 2 times and motor blew I purchased it on sale. Motor blew when used second time. Worst blender ever purchased!!'),
(9071, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-08', 'This is fantastic I love that I can brew one cup or a pot. Every cup is fresh and you never have to worry if you left the coffee pot on. On the weekends we have a booth at a farmer\'s market and I brew a pot. I got it in the Orange and I love the color.'),
(9072, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-19', 'Great Brewer for the price! We bought this on vacation and towed it home, having been at an isolated ski resort with very few services. We have owned the Keurig Mini but it was getting up there in uses. So my hubby took the mini to work and we use this new model at home. I wouldn\'t hesitate to buy it again!'),
(9073, 13, 2, 2, '2015-09-16', 'Liked the Original Keurig Better We had the original Keurig and loved it until it finally died. We purchased the 2.0 and have been so disappointed. It feels like we\'ve regressed instead of making it better. It\'s slower, takes forever to make a cup of coffee, then you only get 10 ounces! There\'s often grounds in the bottom of the cup. Overall, I\'m just bummed that I don\'t have my old Keurig.'),
(9074, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-19', 'Great System The hubby and I use this machine every day, and even more so on the weekends. Great, fresh cup of Joe, but I do wish we would\'ve purchased the level above this one as we underestimated our size and frequency use. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review! You all are the best :)'),
(9075, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Compact, Stylish, Easy to Use I was using a regular coffee brewing machine for my morning rush to work. However, the Keurig 250 is so fast, I use it work mornings and save the fresh ground coffee for the weekend. Excellent product. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review\"'),
(9076, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-05', 'Yep It\'s a Keurig. It makes coffee. That\'s what it said it would do, and that\'s what it does. Employees are happy we bought the machines for them ... I just hope it does\'t slow down productivity. (Ha.)   Nice product. Semi-compact.  Nice features. Easy to use.'),
(9077, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-01', 'I would definitely buy this brewer again This brewer is good for being able to have different drinks throughout the day, especially as a college student. I also like all of the stylish color options that are available. Having the different beverage sizes is a nice bonus as well. I just wish it was a little less noisy when dispensing the drink. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9078, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-07', 'Love my Keurig 2.0! My husband got me the Keurig 2.0 for my birthday this year and it has changed everything! It is even better than my espresso machine, which I now plan on selling! I love how easy it is to make one cup for me, or a carafe for the family when they come over. It\'s so quiet too that I don\'t wake up my son in the morning like I did with the espresso machine. I also love how easy it is to clean it. I can\'t get enough of my Keurig! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9079, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Easy to Use It\'s easy to use'),
(9080, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-11', 'Love it! Husband gifted this to me and I absolutely love it.'),
(9081, 13, 2, 2, '2016-01-13', 'NEEDS SOME IMPROVEMENTS Keeps asking for water after one cup brewed. Water is not hot enough in brewing coffee. Seems a bit loud. Nice colors and size for kitchens.'),
(9082, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-10', 'Perfect size for an apartment I purchased this brewer because it\'s a smaller version but still has all the features of the bigger models. I also loved the fact that it comes in different color options...I bought the strawberry color. It really pops in the kitchen. I am usually running out the door every mirning, and this machine is so quick to heat water and brew that it works perfectly with my lack of time. I would highly recommend this to anyone. I don\'t drink coffee, but the tea comes out tasting great!!!'),
(9083, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Love it! I like Keurigs and when our original K50 finally kicked them bucket after 6 years it was time to get new. K50 is basic and simple. My office has a K425 and I think it\'s a little much since there\'s only two coffee drinkers in the house. I love the strong coffe feature so I chose the K200. My husband is in love with the strong feature and we bought one for his mother for Christmas. She loves the baby blue color and the strong feature as well.'),
(9084, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-21', 'Simple and easy I absolutely LOVE my new Keurig 2.0! It is super easy to use. I love the digital look and that you can choose from multiple oz. settings. I didn\'t drink coffee every day because I hated wasting coffee in a big pot. Now my family can quickly brew a cup anytime of day and nothing goes to waste!'),
(9085, 13, 2, 4, '2016-02-06', 'so far so good we noticed the unit is always warm, but could not find anything in the manual or website about a \"warm\" mode. Is this proper? Please explain this feature, and how to over-ride it if possible. An On-Off switch would be nice.'),
(9086, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-16', 'Love it!!! Absolutely in love with my new Keurig! It works perfectly without any problems. And the color is exactly like the picture.'),
(9087, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'For The Love of The Brew Have you ever wanted to experience exceptional tasting coffee while sitting in your own home without the hassle of driving to your local coffee shop? That is exactly what the Keurig 2.0 delivers! Exceptional tasting coffee and at an affordable price. My wife and I purchased this unit about two weeks ago and simply love it. The ease of use and the range of available flavors makes this a coffee lover\'s dream come true! Plus, not only can we brew a single cup, but we can also brew an entire carafe for guests with the accessory purchased. I want to personally thank Keurig for the free pods for this review. So, what are you waiting for? Get out there and purchase one today and start loving the brew.'),
(9088, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-14', 'don\'t judge a book by its cover easy to use/ makes excellent coffee and iced tea'),
(9089, 13, 2, 2, '2016-01-30', 'This is a so so item I got this for Christmas, gave my old Keurig to my son and wish I would have kept it. My old Keurig would use with any K-Cup no matter who the manufacturer was. I now receive a message with my 2.0 saying my k-cup not compatible. I\'ve received the message that the needle is clogged and the machine is a month old. I would not recommend this to a friend. My daughter received the coffee ninja for Christmas and loves it, wish i would have asked for that.'),
(9090, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-12', 'Help I bought this 3 mos. ago and we\'re very pleased with this product. I need help finding a replacement water filter cartridge for this unit. The replacement I ordered was too tall.'),
(9091, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-05', 'Size doesn\'t always matter. I recently purchased this brewer to replace my Mini Keurig and VUE Brewers. The size is great (like the mini( it fits perfectly on my counter. Unlike the Mini it holds 40 ounces of water which makes it far more convenient. Unlike the VUE, it brews the more popular K-Cup pods, and it will brew a pot of coffee. I really enjoy this brewer. Thanks Keurig.'),
(9092, 13, 2, 2, '2015-08-31', 'Not happy. I use this every morning, and some afternoons. I do enjoy my coffee, but disappointed that the 10 oz size doesn\'t fill the cup. Wish it had a larger size. Coffee is not has hot as the previous Keurig I had. I purchased one before for my granddaughter for college and liked the looks, so this is why I got this one.'),
(9093, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Great gift We had to get the information for the review from my mother-in-law seeing how we bought it for her as a gift .   She loves it .'),
(9094, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'Love this item!!! best coffee maker I have ever owned!!'),
(9095, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-03', 'I LOVE this product! Before this model, I had one of the older models. I absolutely LOVE the touch screen and better brewing options for the k250 though. It\'s an amazing machine. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9096, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-06', 'Keurig luver! The item itself is wonderful! Online ordering and shipping was simple and quick!'),
(9097, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-28', 'Love the Color! So convenient and quick! Very versatile as well! Hot chocolate, coffee or tea! But, I have to admit, it is the color that sold it!!'),
(9098, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-27', 'Excellent customer service! I was most impressed with customer service. I had purchased a Keurig that had been returned and wasn\'t working properly. After several attempts to fix the problem over the phones new machine was promptly sent to us. They stand behind their product.'),
(9099, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-09', 'Coffee never smelled so good! I am so thankful I received this product to test for free from Influenster. I have used Keurig products before but I only used the mini version or an older version my work had. I really like the amount of cup sizes you can brew. I was also pleased that I could fit just about every size of mug under the brewer. Once the water was heated, it brewed coffee very quickly. The only issues I really had with the brewer was you are limited to Keurig K-cups. While there are a lot out there, that definitely limits the cups you can use. Also, while you can brew a carafe, you have to buy it separately. Overall, I am very pleased with the new 2.0 k250 brewer!'),
(9100, 13, 2, 2, '2016-01-05', 'Disappointed I purchased this for my boyfriend for christmas. I\'ve used my mom\'s keurig (another older model) and loved it. She used her own coffee rather than the pods and it always tasted perfect. I purchased the my kcup and carafe to go along with the brewer. Unfortunately no matter what I\'ve tried I can\'t manage to get a strong cup of coffee out of the my kcup. I can\'t speak for the regular pods as we haven\'t used these and never intended to. Is there a trick I don\'t know about? I\'ve searched the internet and discovered many other people have had the same issue. It\'s a real bummer and I guess I\'m just going to have to give in and buy regular pods. Its a shame. I really want to have the freedom to use whatever coffee I want. My sister got us some specialty coffee from a roaster in dallas and I can\'t even get a proper brew from it. It literally looks like tea no matter what I do. I\'ve adjusted the grind and made sure not to over pack the filter. Nothing works. Just be warned if you were thinking of using this for your own coffee. You will be very disappointed.'),
(9101, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-26', 'keurig quick rich brew We love our keurig (glad we didn\'t wait for Christmas)........ have been enjoying several times during the day....... great for tea & hot chocolate...... we are going to buy another while price is so so low for summer cottage'),
(9102, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-10', 'An amazing machine! I use my Keurig 2.0 K250 Brewing System at home for personal use and entertaining friends and fammily. I love the stylish look and design, the resevoir, the fast brewing time, and the availability of really customizing your coffee/beverage! The touch screen is great. And there seeems to be a wide variety of pods available for use with the Keurig 2.0 K250 Brewing System. I have already ordered the caraffee and three kinds of pods to use with it. The only concern I have is that its inability to brew other pods (aka non-Keurig) will limit the consumer and reduce the desire to purchase something that only uses its brand. (Think VCR vs BetaMax, and Tassimo.) I would like to have a caraffe that holds more, but for such a quick brew system I am satisfied. Other than that, I am in love with this machine!'),
(9103, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-12', '2.0 difficulties My 3 year old Keurig started leaking from inside the machine,  so I got this model.   I thought it would be great because it had so many features and brew sizes.   What it failed to mention was that you need special carafe sized k-cups to access everything except up to a 10 oz brew and you can only use Keurig registered cups.   I looked at several stores and only found regular sized cups.  I am unhappy,  so I returned the unit.'),
(9104, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-04', '!!!!WARNING DO NOT BUY!!! READ BELOW I BOUGHT THIS TO REPLACE MY HOME COFFE MAKER (HAMILTON BEECH), THAT MADE LOUSY COFFEE. I HAVE A KEURIG 1.0 IN MY OFFICE THAT USES A REFILLABLE K-CUP W/ AN ADAPTER. THE NEW UNIT (2.0) WILL ONLY WORK W/ KEURIG K-CUPS AND KEURIG DOES NOT MAKE A REFILLABLE K-CUP FOR THE 2.0 SYSTEM AT THIS TIME. I RESOVED ALL PROBLEMS BY PEELING OFF A FRESHLEY BREWED KEURIG K-CUP TOP ( THE HEAT RELEASED THE GLUE ON THE CUP TOP) AND PLACED IT PRINTED SIDE UP ON PAKING TAPE (STICKY SIDE UP) THEN TAPED THAT TAPE WITH PRINTED SIDE UP TO MY REFILLABLE TOP. I THEN INSERTED THE REFILLABLE K-CUP IN THE THE 2.0 UNIT, CLOSED THE TOP, THEN OPENED THE UNIT AND PRESSED THE EXPOSED TAPE ON TO THE EXPOSED BOTTOM OF LID (CLOSING MECHINISM). IT WOKED FINE BUT DID NOT HAVE THE FULL MENU.!!!! TO FIX THAT, I USED A SMALL 1/32 SCALE SLOT CAR MAGNET AND PLACED IT ON THE BOTTOM EDGE OF THE K-CUP INSERT HOLDER. IT HOLDS MAGNETICALLY IN A VERTICLE POSITION AUTOMACTICALLY. VIOLA!!!!!! I NOW HAVE FULL MENU AND CARAFE CAPABILITY AND AM USING MY AFTER MARKET REFILLABLE K-CUP!!! SHAME ON YOU KEURIG!!!!!!!! FOR GETTING GREEDY ABOUT YOUR COFFEE SALES!!! TO RE-DESIGN A QUALITY COFFEE MAKER THAT WILL NOT ALLOW THE CUSTOMER TO USE THE COFFEE OF HIS CHOICE IS UNCONSCIENABLE AND DOWN RIGHT WRONG!!!! WHEN I NEED TO REPLACE EITHER OF MY 2 KEURIGS IT WILL BE WITH A DIFFFEERNT BRAND THAT IS NOT PROPRITARY!!! KEURIG HAS LOST MY BUSINESS FOREVER!!!! FOR BEING GREEDY AND UNETHICAL!!!!'),
(9105, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Not that HOT! This is a good coffee maker. I prefer my starbucks drinks at child friendly temps. This machine is nice because it does not get that hot. I love that fact, some people may not.'),
(9106, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-02', 'Love the convenience of this brewer I love the convenience and versatility of this machine. It\'s great when I want a quick cup of coffee with no hassle or cleanup. The size of this machine is just right. It doesn\'t take up too much counter space, but still holds a decent amount of water and accommodates most cup sizes. The violet color is very fun and bright. The \"strong\" setting on the brewer is a very nice feature and does seem to help provide a more flavorful cup of coffee. The only thing I wish this particular model had was an Auto Off feature. But I will gladly sacrifice that feature for the more compact size (and the violet color). Overall, very satisfied with my purchase. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9107, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-09', 'Low foot print excellent customer service Love the stylish color and low foot print. Customer service was excellent to work with. Makes an awesome cup of coffee too.'),
(9108, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-25', 'Great Brewer great brewer I use it everyday for coffee and tea.'),
(9109, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-07', 'Highlight Of My Morning! I LOVE my Keurig 2.0! I drink coffee EVERY morning, and having the choice to brew one cup, or a whole pot is so convenient. On mornings that my husband doesn\'t want coffee-and I don\'t know how he survives the day-I can make just one for myself. And I love that I can make a 10oz mug, some single serve machines only make a 6oz cup! But mornings when both of us want coffee, I can make a whole carafe, which is very nice. The only thing I would change, is having the 10oz option for dispensing hot water for times when I want a cup of tea. But other than that, I absolutely love it!'),
(9110, 14, 2, 1, '2015-03-30', 'Unhappy Granny The product was missing some parts and it starting leaking with the first use.'),
(9111, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'Anonymous I bought this for my Mom--she kept mooning over it for months--and when I found this in red, I had to get it for her. She LOVES it. She is not very tech savvy, but she has had no problem learning how to use it. I have bought her several different kinds of coffees to use, and she has enjoyed trying the different varieties.  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(9112, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-11', 'Love my Keurig! I really love this Keurig!  The one and only downside is not being able to use all pods.'),
(9113, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-10', 'Second Keurig. This is my second Keurig.  I thought it was going to be smaller than the old one, but it\'s not.  I have a problem turning the machine off--pressing the little tiny on-screen button is difficult.  It\'s a little tricky filling the reservour since it is behind the coffee maker.'),
(9114, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'So pretty I bought this last week. I love the oasis color and it looks great in my kitchen! It works great and makes a perfect cup of coffee every time!'),
(9115, 13, 2, 2, '2016-02-04', 'K250 is just OK Keurig has great products, but the K250 is a bit off target. My 1st unit had to be returned unused because it was defective. Great customer service replaced it quickly. My second unit works but I often still get a message the needle is clogged even when the unit is empty. It quickly resets by cycling the handle up the close again to clear it. The rear reservoir is not convenient. It was a gift, but next time I\'ll definitely get a model with a side reservoir.'),
(9116, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Great Product for its Compact Size I bought this Keurig 2.0 to replace our old Mr.Coffee Keurig brewer. Completely happy with the purchase, it gets really hotter compared to the old one and is really easy to use. The size is perfect since we use it on the boat where we live all summer. We have both the older larger model and the Newer 2.0 larger models also, could not be any happier with all the keurig products!'),
(9117, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-06', 'Perfect for me It\'s the perfect size for the space on my counter.  It\'s of great quality and works extremely well.'),
(9118, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-04', 'K200 Works very well love the touch screen, kid friendly as well as adult friendly'),
(9119, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'great pick I would highly recommend this to anyone, it works great!'),
(9120, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-29', 'Perfect Size first \"I would like to say \"thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review\".I purchased my Keurig in white. It is tasteful and the perfect size for my kitchen. Coffee tastes great and brews quickly. The canister holds a good amount of water, so I don\'t feel like I am always having to refill it. Perfect for morning half asleep coffee drinkers. Best part don\'t have to worry if I left the coffee pot on. When I leave my house.'),
(9121, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-19', 'Easy to use I use this everyday, makes amazing coffee.'),
(9122, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-17', 'Great Machine I love this machine and how easy it is to make all of my favorite beverages. there are lots of different k-cup pods you can get. Also like that it is fairly small and doesnt take up too much room on my counter. Makes a quick cup of coffee or any other beverage.'),
(9123, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Keurig is awesome! I love my new keurig and the price was awesome ! I got it on sale , and they had a one day only extra 30% off and you got a 15$ target gift card!  Couldn\'t pass it up!'),
(9124, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-11', 'Pros + Conts The Keurig 2.0 is DEFINITELY an update from the old-fashioned (haha) one. Here is a list of the pros (and very few cons) of the Keurig 2.0: Pros: Screen that tells you what is going on. This is AWESOME for someone who is impatient and skeptical, like me. If it weren\'t for the screen on the new Keurig 2.0 telling me that it was preheating, I might go into a panic, wondering if I did something wrong. And it is is touch screen. This is awesome. Water amount options. Via the touch screen you can select four (I think the old Keurig machines only had 3) different pour options: 4 oz (for super-strong), 6 oz, 8 oz, 10 oz. I, a coffee fiend, went for the strong-ish 6 oz pour. Add hot water option. Turns out that the 6 oz pour did not fill my mug enough, so I was was pleased that there was an option to add just hot water to your cup. Even after adding hot water my cup of coffee was still really good and strong. I was honestly impressed with the Keurig coffee. Descaling solution. The machine came with descaling solution, which is great because if you want your coffee machine to last, you need to descale it often. A bunch of free pods. The Keurig 2.0 came with a bunch (I think ~30) free pods in all different varieties. Very generous of them! My husband even tried the tea and liked it. Very sleek and compact. This machine looks great on the counter in our small, seminary-housing apartment. It fit in the place I usually keep my blender (which means it is very compact). It fit well below our cabinets, as well. Instruction manual in multiple languages and has lots of good info. Including giving you information about recycling K-cups. And...perhaps my favorite: it is polite. This Keurig is noticeably polite! It says \"Welcome\", \"Please\", \"Enjoy\"... etc. Very polite programing, thank you very much. Less dishes. At the end of the day, all you have to clean is your mug. Cons: No Carafe. I was excited about the coffee pot feature of the Keurig 2.0, which will be great when we have guests over. However the Carafe is sold separately, which kind of disappointed me. Froze. Because it is now run by a more complicated computer (because of the touch screen, etc.) this means there is more room for bugs. My machine got caught in a loop and was stuck \"preheating\" for about 10 minutes before I realized it was not really preheating. At that point I unplugged the machine to give it a restart. When I plugged it back in it started reheating right away. So, as you can see, there are very few cons and lots of pros! I will consider giving this as a gift for some upcoming weddings! The product is great.'),
(9125, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Keurig This coffee maker is a must have. I love it. I never go a day without using it.'),
(9126, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-20', 'very happy! we use the Keurig everyday. It is easy to use and compact. Really happy with this purchase. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(9127, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-24', 'Can\'t stay away! I have an older Keurig that I got when I began college, and I also recently got the new Keurig Rivo. But my older Keurig was too big for my new counter space to fit, so I got this one and its AMAZING. It\'s so small, I LOVE the touch screen, it holds all of my old KCups and it holds so much water for it\'s little size! Keurig has had my love since day 1 and they never disappoint!'),
(9128, 13, 2, 2, '2015-11-01', 'Concerned I just gave this unit to my son as a gift. He has already had issues. I am very disappointed as we have been Elite users for over 4 years. What am I going to do now?'),
(9129, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-18', 'Not loving this I am sad that this machine does not live up to the hype. First and foremost is the fact that the pods I had from previous machine do not work w this model. That leaves me with dozens of now wasted pods,money gone. Next is the no shut off feature( am now unplugging) which not only uses electricity,but I find the machine stays very warm,which worried me. I also am disappointed that I no longer get a full cup of coffee,but maybe half to 3/4 that I got w my single serve. As I have tossed the box and packing slip(my bad,thought it would be keeper like others) am seriously considerin g purchasing another brand of coffee maker/Brewer and putting this away in storage(maybe bring out if having major company). Did I also mention this is much noisier while brewing than previous models?! Sorry Keurig,this misses the mark with me.'),
(9130, 13, 2, 2, '2017-01-29', 'Leaks Love my keurig, but it leaks from the back. I\'ve heard of others having this issue also. I\'m just not sure how to fix it. I have the purple one & i love the look & it makes coffee fine, just wasting water & making a mess from the leak.'),
(9131, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-11', 'Small but handy I have owned Keurigs in the past and loved them. This one is great because of its small design. I usually only drink coffee once a day, so this has been a great addition to my office at work. It\'s compact and easy to use. The only downfall is how small the water tank is, but that doesn\'t bother me much given how much coffee I drink.'),
(9132, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-29', 'Keurig K475 I use this machine for my morning coffee and I love it its so convient it fits perfectly in my kitchen counter I love it'),
(9133, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-09', 'Great coffee maker This is an awesome coffee maker.  The ease of use is a big positive.  I love this.'),
(9134, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-22', 'GREAT BUY! I upgraded from an older 2 cup size Keurig and ABSOLUTELY love this machine (Keurig K200)! My husband who was anti-Keurig and only used the normal coffee maker even LOVES it! I bought the reusable coffee filter as well and it works great! We had a 1/2 container of coffee still and I was very pleased that this filter will help us use the coffee we already have! 5 STARS all the way! I HIGHLY recommend this maker!'),
(9135, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Daughter\'s gift I bought this as a Christmas gift for my daughter, she loves it. The purple color is beautiful!'),
(9136, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-25', 'its the perfect color love it'),
(9137, 13, 2, 2, '2017-01-01', 'This Keurig does not fit standard cups I bought this beautiful keurig...was so excited and used it with my standard keurig k-cups not knowing...it did not fit.  The k-cup opened and coffee grinds got everywhere and what a mess it was.   Just know that this keurig machine needs its own kind of K-cups!!! Don\'t make the same mistake I made. Otherwise it is a beautiful coffee machine.'),
(9138, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-14', 'unpredictable machine even though some pods are labeled for use. such as Meijer brand. machine clogs up and coffee grounds go all over machine inside. went through 3 machines in 3 weeks. still not right. tech support even said that our filtered water was too clean. we replaced a 10+year old bun coffee maker that still works. thought this would be more convenient. we like the variety of pods. just wish that if it says keurig brewed on package. it would work properly.'),
(9139, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-01', 'Perfect For A College Student!!!!!1 I absolutely love my Keurig!! I picked the color purple because it matches my room, perfectly. I really like how I can make up to 4 cups of coffee!!!! It is for sure needed for school!! and for it being the newest model it comes at a GOOD Price!!!!!'),
(9140, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-04', 'Mom loves it Easy to use, compact, and quick coffee'),
(9141, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-25', 'AWESOME This product is super easy to use and brews drinks in less than a minute. Whether I\'m rushing out the door, or just trying to enjoy my breakfast, the 40 mL reservoir allows me to be ready for either occasion. This new sleek version also fits nicely in my kitchen and allows me to save space for my endless amount of K-Cups that this machine can brew! AMAZING!!!'),
(9142, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-18', 'Love my keurig! Love the color oasis. Pre heats quickly so it makes its better then warming up water on stove for coffee, soups or anything else. So far so good.'),
(9143, 13, 2, 2, '2015-08-10', 'Disappointed I have the Keurig elite that I use daily. I\'m very disappointed that the K cups won\'t work in the K2.0 250 that I purchased today. My husband isn\'t real happy that now I have to buy different Kpods. Also would like to be able to get the filter so I can use my own coffee. Very very disappointed.'),
(9144, 13, 2, 3, '2016-12-15', 'Not what I thought! I purchased this, sight unseen as a gift. I have an older model that is larger but has been a great coffee maker! This is part of the reason I gave one as a gift. However, after seeing this model in the store and some of the other models for that matter, I have to say I am VERY disappointed in the quality. It is mostly plastic including the handle (where mine is metal). It doesn\'t feel like it will last for very long especially if you have someone that drinks a lot of coffee. Hopefully I am wrong. I just made sure to tell them to register it on the website just in case.'),
(9145, 13, 2, 5, '2015-09-26', 'Great addition to my office This Keurig was a gift from my husband for my office. I love the color! I use it multiple times a week, sometimes twice a day. I have had no issues. The Keurig functions properly and brews very quickly. I\'m very happy with this product!  Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9146, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-30', 'Perfect coffee for all lifestyles! I first fell in love with Keurig machines at an old job where a coworker had a machine. It was great because I had a night shift and could get the perfect fix of caffeine when all the shops were closed. When she left and took her Keurig with her I was devastated. The lack of coffee at my fingertips frightened me. Luckily I have since convinced my roommates to purchase the K200 brewing system and life couldn\'t be better. First off I have to say Keurig themselves are a pretty awesome group. I was using a coupon to purchase this brewer but the color I wanted to purchase was sold out. I emailed support to ask if there was any chance that color might be back in stock before the coupon ran out. Although the dates didn\'t quite work out their customer support responded quickly and was super friendly. They even gave me a coupon for a free box of pods because I was sad about the color being sold out. Speaking of colors, can I just say how awesome it they have such a variety of colors available! I love pops of color and have always been a little bored by the monotone colors available for basic kitchen appliances. It was super exciting to have the option to choose between so many fun and attractive color choices. But enough about it\'s appearance, how does this thing work? Super easily! I\'m no master chef and often get stressed out thinking about making things in the kitchen. Coffee is one of those things that everyone has very specific requirements about how they want them to taste, and if you don\'t get it right they\'re doubly cranky because they lack caffeine. This machine is amazing because everyone can customize the size and strength of their cup of joe. I haven\'t used it yet but you can brew a carafe for a larger party, or if you really just need all the coffee ever. I love this thing because although I don\'t work as late as I once did, I\'m still on an opposite schedule than my roommates. With a larger coffee pot I would either be faced with drinking old, cold coffee or trying to figure out the science and ratio of water to coffee to brew a smaller batch in those big jugs. It never ended well for me with mostly watery coffee. Now when I roll out of bed mid morning I get the perfect amount of fresh hot coffee with minimal effort. I should also mention I am incredibly lazy which makes this machine a god send, no measurements or leaving machine warmers on for hours or daily clean ups of a pot. The ease of popping a cup in and pressing 3 buttons makes my mornings that much happier. Also no fear of leaving the warmer on and potentially burning down your house is a plus. We once had to turn around in a snow storm to go turn off our old coffee maker. Cleanup with this machine is a breeze! About once a week I wipe down the sides of the machine since coffee sometimes splashes up, and give a good wash to the drip tray. The water tank is pretty small and easily monitored for any potential buildup that would need to be washed out. We use this machine so often I doubt anything has time to build up! The only slight negative I have, is I am a little weary to brew things like iced tea through this in fears of it somehow tasting like coffee. I know the easy fix is to run a cycle or 2 of hot water to get rid of any remaining odors, but as I mentioned before I am lazy and not desperate to have quick iced tea at my finger tips. In my mind Keurig can do no wrong! And although Keurig is compensating me with some k cups for writing this I would gladly tell anyone within earshot about the wonders of this machine! So small it can easily fit anywhere in your kitchen! Fun colors and the fastest coffee in all the land. You will not regret one second of your purchase and might kick yourself for not getting one sooner. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9147, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-05', 'Awesome product! I recently purchased this item for my girlfriend. I must say that I absolutely love the rapid shipment of the product. Received in less than 4 days.   The design of the product is awesome. The slim, elegant design makes her counter-top not look cluttered with the Keurig system on it.   I use Keurig at work all the time and love the quality. Nothing beats freshly brewed coffee, but Keurig offers a rather good tasting quick-brew for your buck.'),
(9148, 14, 2, 4, '2014-12-20', 'blender review I have been very pleased with this blender. I got it at a great price. I chops ice much quicker than my last blender.'),
(9149, 13, 2, 1, '2016-02-05', 'DON\'T BUY 2.0!!!!!!!!! The machine is very picky and sometimes it will not accept a pod even though it is stamped 2.0. Hard to take time to fiddle with it just to have your coffee in the morning! I am going back to my old one that is much more reliable. Total waste of money!!!!!!!!!!'),
(9150, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-28', 'Great Quality Great for making coffee all day/everyday!'),
(9151, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Love my Keurig! I wasn\'t a huge coffee drinker when I decided to purchase my Keurig, but now it\'s so easy, I drink it every day. There\'s so many varieties of coffee to choose from, and the Keurig makes making a single cup super fast and easy. I\'m extremely happy with my purchase and would recommend one to anyone. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9152, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-08', 'Perfect I\'ve been wanting a Keurig for some time to replace my I\'ll old fashioned coffee maker, but I wanted something small.  This version is perfect for me.  I love the compact design and easy of use.'),
(9153, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-30', 'LOVE IT!!! My husband bought this for me for Christmas, it was the main gift that I wanted, & I am SO GLAD that I got it! It worked great right out of the box, the instructions for setup are simple, & I just love the loads of varieties of coffees to choose from. I\'ve had so much fun trying out the different flavors, now I can\'t wait to get up every morning to make some coffee! I\'ve had NO PROBLEMS whatsoever, & I would definitely recommend this product to anyone who asked me. I\'m going to be upgrading to the K500 model next!'),
(9154, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-28', 'My New go to housewarming gift! Keurig has gone above and beyond! I truly love this new machine. We are a large family of 6 and hate having to make our cups one by one it\'s time consuming. With this new machine we can make an ENTIRE pot of coffee! This has cut down on our coffee time believe it or not. We finally have a way to entertain guest without having to pass out coffee one cup at a time. It\'s so much easier to make a pot of coffee and keep the flow going. The water tank is also a plus. We can make more pots and not have to constantly refill the tank. The fact that we can make a lot of coffee or individually make them as the day progresses is a huge plus and the winning factor.'),
(9155, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-28', 'This model has awesome upgrades/features! We bought the original Keurig right after they came out and used it for quite some time. We have the 2.0, and love all of the new features! Pros: Quietso much quieter than the first version. Lots more options when brewing. You can opt for a \"strong\" brew, change the amount of water used, or (my favorite) just heat water! Love that feature for brewing tea. This version has a carafe that you can fill with using special pods. I\'d love to try this out for brewing a large quantity of coffee, but it was not included with my package. I love that you can descale your machine. We had the original version of the Keurig and this was not something that was mentioned/recommended (if I remember right). Such a great way to keep your machine running great. Cons: The water chamber signals needing to be refilled when it still has 1/3 of the water left in it. At our house, my husband and I drink multiple cups of coffee each day, so it needs to be refilled frequently. The coffee is not equal to a strong cup you\'d get from an espresso machine (which is what we used to make coffee prior to getting this Keurig.) But, if you like coffee, don\'t need a crazy strong brew (even using the strong feature), this machine is quiet, easy to clean, and easy peasy to use. Such a great product (especially when comparing to the original one!).'),
(9156, 13, 2, 2, '2015-10-08', 'Disappointed I resisted buying a Keurig for years, because I hated the cost and waste (still do). With that said, it does make decent coffee and is super convenient. However, this new system clogs constantly (like, on the 3rd use!). I finally figured out that if I used the Rogers cups (the ones with paper bottoms instead of plastic), it no longer clogged...and tasted better! I resent the fact that this new system won\'t let you fill your own cups, when in my experience it\'s their own cups breaking the darned thing in the first place. Google \"Freedom Clip\" for a workaround.');
INSERT INTO `Reviews` (`Review_ID`, `Product_ID`, `Site_ID`, `Star_Rating`, `Date_Of_Post`, `Review_Text`) VALUES
(9157, 13, 2, 5, '2016-11-05', 'More Compact Design is Fabulous Love the new, smaller design, and the Oasis color suits my tastes perfectly.  I been considering a Keurig for quite some time, but have a smaller kitchen with limited counter space, so finally decided to take the plunge.  We use pods when we only want a single cup, and your own basket when we make a carafe.  The coffee is always consistent in flavor and strength....we couldn\'t be happier with this purchase!'),
(9158, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-15', 'Great Coffeemaker! This is my first Keurig and it is wonderful! So easy to use and very fast. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9159, 13, 2, 4, '2016-01-05', 'Customer Service Excels I had problems with my brewer, it would not brew anything! All my pods were the correct ones from Keurig, and it would not even brew hot water... After talking with customer service, they had me explain the problem and had me run through some troubleshooting. The problem was not resolved. Customer service then decided that they would send me a whole new machine. I am currently waiting for it to arrive, but I am very pleased with customer service. Review to come once the new machine arrives.'),
(9160, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-30', 'Love it I love my new Keurig. I wasn\'t much of a coffee drinker but since I started working the morning shifts, I need something to help get my day going. I love this product because it\'s so quick. Just pop the pod in and within seconds, you have a fresh cup of brew. I sometimes feel like I\'m wasting coffee because I can only brew up to 10oz on this machine and that doesn\'t even come close to filling up my 16oz coffee cup. I usually have to brew twice or use a second pod. I would defiantly recommend this product to family and friends. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9161, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Keurig Got It Right Keurig finally got it right. Very satisfied with the machine.'),
(9162, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-22', 'Great Coffee Maker So Easy to Use. The coffee tastes great!! Not One bad brew yet. Disclosure :\"thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review\"'),
(9163, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-17', 'Fast, Easy, Convenient I have been using this several times a week since I got it. It is perfect before class. It is cheaper than going to a coffee shop and faster, too.'),
(9164, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-21', 'The carafe makes this work for me I did not buy a Keurig prior because I hadn\'t researched it and no friends had the carafe option on theirs (I drink 2-3, 10 oz. cups each morning + a single cup after dinner). This model solved that issue, plus offered the \"strong\" brew option. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9165, 14, 2, 5, '2015-08-11', 'blender good....................'),
(9166, 13, 2, 1, '2016-09-28', 'Doesn\'t work! I bought this one to replace another, more expensive brewer, that just quit working after a couple years with very little use.  Received this product and right out of the box, it doesn\'t work either.  So aggravated with myself for again doing business with Keurig but I simply like the concept, when it works.  They are sending me a replacement, fingers crossed!!'),
(9167, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-29', 'My First Keurig! I received this as a gift and LOVE it! I have been wanting a K2.0 since they first came out. I can drink my coffee flavor of choice and so can my husband. Best gift ever!!!'),
(9168, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'Definitely worth every penny Use it every morning and pleased with every aspect. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9169, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-13', 'Keurig 2.0 We purchased this as a gift for our daughter so she has only had it for a few days. So far, she likes it and it works well. It is a bit bulky and takes up more room than she would have liked. Overall, I would say she is pleased with her gift. We purchased the K-Cup for her so that she could use regular coffee because the pods are so expensive. I read one review that said you cannot use the K-Cup but that is not true. It is made for this machine. Hopefully, it this Keurig will last her a long time and the touch screen controls will not be a problem down the line. I love the color choices and would recommend it to others at this time.'),
(9170, 13, 2, 2, '2015-12-02', 'Returning mine Very disappointed to find that the brewer won\'t accept other brand Kcups. I have some Kuerig favorites, but I also have some that are not Keurig brand (mainly Camerons) and the brewer will not accept them. Such a shame, monopoly is the way of the world, even in Keurig world....'),
(9171, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-26', 'Super cute. Got the light blue one and it\'s super cute. Easy to use and most importantly small enough to fit in my small dorm room. Only thing is that it\'s a little pricey, but I guess you pay for convenience.'),
(9172, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-18', 'Will be returning due to limits on coffee brands I purchased this as a Christmas gift for my husband, to replace a Keurig Mini that has been positively plagued by problems with grounds continually clogging the needle, etc. It\'s so disappointing to see in other reviews that while this is a new and improved product, the malfunction continues to be a recurring problem. But the biggest reason that I am returning this machine without giving it to my husband is the restriction on which coffee pods can be used in the machine. We like to use Dunkin coffee, among others. Though this restriction on Keurig\'s part is a classic capitalist move, it just seems downright unAmerican. It\'s laughable to see Keurig respond to complaints about this limitation with the comment, \"We\'re sorry to hear you have k-cup pods that will not brew in your new 2.0 K250. \" They\'re sorry to hear it? It\'s exactly what they wanted. They designed it that way. Sorry, but I just can\'t support that kind of corporate malfeasance.'),
(9173, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-12', 'Great way to drink coffee I bought this unit for a gift for someone and I liked it so much that I decided to keep it for my family.  We are so happy that we did not give  it away. We are enjoying many different blends of coffee and we are looking forward to trying teas. The coffee is very hot and this  machine is so easy to use.'),
(9174, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-27', 'Love it! I got my Keurig from my brother for Christmas and I love it. I also received a big variety pack of K-Cups and a reusable K-Cup as well. I absolutely love it. I live in an apartment with a small kitchen, and I love kitchen gadgets, so I was worried it wouldn\'t fit, however, it\'s very compact and fits in a small space. I only drink one small cup of coffee a day, so this is perfect for me, but I intend to get the carafe so that I can use it when I have company over. I notice a lot of people complaining that not all K-Cups work in the 2.0, and that\'s true- I got some Crazy Cups in my variety pack that don\'t work, so I just open them, dump the grounds into the reusable cup and brew. Throw away the top, and recycle the cup (since Crazy Cups are recyclable). Additionally, if someone wants more coffee, there\'s always the option to brew a carafe! The only cons about this Keurig, that I\'ve found so far, are easily remedied. I love my Keurig!'),
(9175, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-22', 'Simple & Compact I love it the new Keurig 2.0 K250 brewer! We had an older model Keurig from 5 years ago and this new brewer really leaves that one in the dust. It\'s sleek, compact and perfect for those who want any size of coffee or tea during the day. It\'s also FAST!'),
(9176, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-15', 'Best Keurig so far! I use this machine daily! I love it. Very quick. Gives such a great brew of coffee. The temperature is always perfect. I\'m so excited to have this machine apart of my kitchen. We are now thinking of purchasing one for our camper! My only complaint is the noise. Its a bit loud but only for a few moments and its worth it. I absolutely love my Keurig 2.0 K250.'),
(9177, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-24', 'Don\'t judge until you try I love how it has the screen up on top so you can control everything and how there is many different flavor a of coffees and teas'),
(9178, 13, 2, 1, '2016-04-01', 'Brew Interrupted I received this coffee pot for a gift. After several cups of coffee i started getting the message: Brew interrupted. I called the company and they sent me a new one. After the 4th cup it started saying the same thing again. This time they sent me a new part. After the 5th cup of coffee it started doing the same thing again. Once again they sent me a new one. If it messes up again, I\'m going to insist on a different model. I am not happy with this one at all.'),
(9179, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-20', 'COFFE SMELLS AND TASTE LIKE PLASTIC!!!! I\'m very disappointed with my new Keurig machine. I was excited to make a cup of coffee until it smelt like burnt plastic and tasted like it also. I went on line to see if other people have had the same problem and they have ... they say to flush it with vinegar ... well, this is what I\'ve been doing instead if enjoying a cup of coffee!!! So far no improvement ... looks like it\'s getting returned to the store!'),
(9180, 13, 2, 1, '2015-10-06', 'Very Disappointed This is our second Keurig purchase. We loved our first Keurig and after it quit working we purchased the Keurig 2.0 without hesitation. Unfortunately, it has been a huge disappointment. The coffee is not very hot and there have been coffee grounds in every cup. Needless to say, we will be returning this brewer. Hopefully, we can find some other replacement. I wish it worked as well as our first brewer, it was fantastic.'),
(9181, 13, 2, 3, '2015-08-12', 'Good Brewer for everyday coffee drinker I just recently purchased the Keurig 2.0 Brewer. I can just pop the pod in and get a single cup of coffee. I like that I can choose the cup size and the strength of my coffee . The only complaints I have is the brewer is larger than it looked online when I was ordering it, it doesn\'t automatically turn off, and it has to preheat the water before making your drink. \"Thanks, Kuerig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(9182, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-26', 'Christmas nightmare! I have a Keurig Vue brewer that I love. This thing was a Christmas present from my daughters. Shame on you for selling this piece of junk that got stopped up after one use. Now I can\'t use it. I had to go back to my old Keurig this morning, the day after Christmas. Calling up for help the day after Christmas would probably be a nightmare so I am returning it.'),
(9183, 13, 2, 3, '2015-11-27', 'please be aware I was in love with my keurigs and their customer service until I bought the red pot and found out the I can not use my old pods because they have coded the machine to read the lids and it will not brew my older starbucks pods. It gives you a message that you are not using their product. REALLY why do we need this. I am user of their coffee service and have only bought quality pods for all my pots I don\'t know if all their systems are this way but I am so disappointed. I found this out when I called because I couldn\'t get to brew. So please be aware you may be throwing away perfectly good coffee not something I can afford.'),
(9184, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-02', 'Coffee=happiness Perfect size for my daily morning coffee. I love the stylish color options! Hope to get many many uses out of it!!!!!'),
(9185, 13, 2, 5, '2016-09-18', 'We needed a replacement.. I bought a new coffee maker in May. Unfortunately, we had to plunge it multiple times a week. It took one call to them to have a replacement in the mail, as promised. I am impressed they stand behind their product and did what they say they will do.  Thank you, Keurig.. for being an excellent and honorable company.'),
(9186, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-03', 'Sometimes won\'t turn on... I was given this product two months ago as a gift. I use it almost every morning. About a month in to having it, the power button started acting finicky. Now it is once a week the Keurig will not turn on. The power button is digital on the touch screen - not sure if it\'s a screen issue or a power issue but it is a very annoying problem to have the coffee maker not turn on. In order to make it work, I have to leave the Keurig unplugged for an hour after being non-responsive, and it then will turn on right away.'),
(9187, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-17', 'love it I have had the mr coffee one cup for 4 years never had a keurig, im loving it so much. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review!!!'),
(9188, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-15', 'Love  it Great price,quality,and easy to use.....'),
(9189, 13, 2, 1, '2016-05-29', 'High Maintenance Brewer, Do Not Buy. I have owned this brewer for 1 year and it s very high maintenance. Constant cleaning is required. I use the filter and descaling solution, but it still doesn\'t pour a consistent cup of coffee. It is preprogrammed to ask after emptying the used cup, \"Would you like to dispense hot water\"? Now why would it do that other than to help clean the puncture tube since it clogs all the time. And why would a coffee maker come with a device specifically designed to help clean/declog the tip. We have an original Kuerig at home that gets much more use and it never clogs, and always brews the perfect cup of coffee. This 2.0 is like a bad movie sequel. Worst mistake I ever made with coffee Brewers. I will say that customer service is always very helpful. But who wants a product that always needs maintenance? They really is nothing good or great about this product. It is an epic failure. I bought a used older style keurig and it performs much better and never clogs.'),
(9190, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-11', 'Great new brewer I use this product everyday for my morning and afternoon coffee. It is great because it is much quieter than the older model I used to own. I don\'t have to worry about waking up the rest of the house trying to make a cup of coffee. I do miss using my refillable K-Cups but this one now makes bigger and if you like stronger cups of coffee so I am all in!'),
(9191, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-20', 'My Eco-friendly cups did not work Returning, I only use Keurig if the cups are recyclable. They are not compatible with this machine.'),
(9192, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-26', 'Love my Keurig Received my new Keurig and love it...had a Vue in the past. This one is faster, guicker and hotter. More avaiable K cups to choose from plus as an added bonus ...you have the carafe. Have been a Keurig \"user\" for years and this is my favorite'),
(9193, 13, 2, 3, '2015-12-11', 'Very disappointed I read the reviews about the pods, but I knew all the pods I had said, \"Keurig\" on the box and were the same companies that Keurig is partnered with, so I didn\'t think my five boxes of pods would go to waste. Apparently I was wrong and they won\'t work in my brewer. These pods are not inexpensive and I feel that I have wasted a lot of money trying to upgrade my model. I think Keurig should have really thought this through better. Why alienate your own customers this way. I can\'t believe anyone is going to be happy throwing away all their unused pods. If my pods would have worked I would have been happy with my purchase.'),
(9194, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-18', 'Not too shabby! Love my new Keurig! The only annoyance was the lack of any auto on/off settings. My husband sets our old Keurig to turn on and warm up before work so he can hit brew and go on his way. There is no option for that with the 2.0 k250. Otherwise it\'s a great machine!'),
(9195, 13, 2, 2, '2015-07-04', 'Disappointment My husband and I need four cups each morning. Pouring one at a time and rushing back and forth to the kitchen to produce each cup is a total pain. Also, I should not say cup, I should say mug and we only get a partial mug full out of each pod. I am waiting to get the gizmo that allows me to use my own coffee and maybe then I will be happier. Meantime, even though my friend bought me this machine, I am not happy with it at all because of the small amount dispensed with each pod. The pods too are expensive. Reminds me of getting a free printer with my computer and then having to use expensive ink cartridges.'),
(9196, 13, 2, 1, '2015-11-24', 'Terrible I had my 2.0 for about two months when it started to just drip coffee, got stuck in preheat even after the tank was full. I knew it was going to die on us when it wasn\'t make a full 8 or 10 oz cup, but I was excepting to get at least a year or two. I returned it thinking maybe it was just defective, but now two days later, we are experiencing the same issue! I will be returning it again and we will NOT be getting another. Back to the old fashioned coffee pot!'),
(9197, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Nice little machine I find that it is easier to use a pitcher of water to refill the water rather than detaching it from the machine, filling it, and then trying to reattach.'),
(9198, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-22', 'Quick, Easy & So, So Good! I am a recent (3 year) daily coffee drinker. I am loving this Keurig 2.0! It is so easy, quick and the end result is a hot, wonderful cup of coffee. I absolutely love that I can use my travel coffee mug with this model. It makes it very convenient. There are so many KCup options, my head spins! The only downside, which really, isn\'t a downside, is that the 2.0 is a little noisy - but, it\'s quick, so no really a big deal. I\'m in awe at how quickly it gets hot and is ready to go! Enjoy!'),
(9199, 13, 2, 4, '2016-04-26', 'just OK I\'ve trying to register my unit but it won\'t work, this model doesn\'t even show up in the selection. Hope it doesn\'t break or I won\'t get my warranty.'),
(9200, 13, 2, 5, '2015-10-04', 'Great Machine, great colors I love the colors and that it is compact but still hold water. This replaced my single cup machine at work.'),
(9201, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-28', 'I love it! I absolutely love my new keurig. my husband and I received this as a wedding present and we use it every day. We save so much money and don\'t waste nearly as much money and coffee. This is really help having because we like two different kinds of coffee. thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9202, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-29', 'Keurig 200 Purchased as a Christmas gift for my daughter and her family.  She wanted a maker that would be able to make 12oz size cups and this one met that need.  She stated it was easy to set up, likes that it holds a large amount of water and still is not too large.   Her only negative was that it seemed a little louder than other Keurigs she has used but that\'s not a problem.   Was a great deal as I purchased it during a sale and recieved several discounts off the price..'),
(9203, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-21', 'Right out of the box with a problem I followed all the instructions for setting up the unit and it has not been on \"preheat\" for 30 minutes. This is ridiculous.'),
(9204, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-04', 'Great machine but needs a \"one cup\" setting I got this on sale so the value was great but it wouldn\'t have been at the full price. I bought the little basket that allows you to make your own coffee and that is wonderful. I use that every day and my kids love the hot chocolate.   My issue is that after I make my one cup, it reheats the water and I can\'t tell it not to. When I\'m only making one cup, I unplug it so save energy so it doesn\'t reheat the water. Wish there was a setting so I could tell it that.   Otherwise, I love it and the size and turquoise color are great.'),
(9205, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-19', 'Disappointing Do not waste your money.  This is my 3rd Keurig coffeemaker and it is going back. My other ones just took some getting used to, but the new design is just not worth the hassle. Halfway through the brewing cycle it quit, giving me an error message that would not go away no matter what I did to correct it. The water reservoir is half the capacity of my old one and the cup sizes are smaller, too. Until they redesign it, I won\'t be getting another one.'),
(9206, 13, 2, 3, '2015-06-27', 'Miss my platinum brewer!! The new brewer does not allow for a 12 oz cup size, unlike my previous Keurig Platinum brewer. While the carafe that was included is nice to have if you want to brew a pot of coffee, I bought a Keurig to brew single cups. I would rather have the option of brewing a 12 oz cup over the carafe. I don\'t like the design of the reservoir as it is difficult to fill..'),
(9207, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-15', 'Nice improvements I had the Keurig mini before purchasing the 250 and was having problems with grounds getting into the cup. I like how this new machine includes a cleaning ball and seems easier to clean all the parts. The touch display is nice so it is very easy to select cup size and strength. This model is a great improvement.'),
(9208, 13, 2, 1, '2016-07-15', 'Worst Experience of My Life My boyfriend and I bought this brewer about 2 days ago and we have been going through heck to get the pods for it. Everywhere we go, no one has them. Even the pods that were included weren\'t compatible. It says here that the brewer works with K-Pods, K-Mug, and K-Carafe. It works with none of these! I went on the suggested website (keurig.com/oops) and watched a video that said the brewer only works with Keurig 2.0 pods, and we could find these NOWHERE. We even went on the website to try to order some, but we see nothing that\'s compatible. We ended up buying an OFFICIAL Keurig 2.0 do-it-yourself kind of K-cup, and tried using that. Same error message. We are BEYOND frustrated. I can\'t believe the experience we\'ve had in only two days.'),
(9209, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-09', 'Love this machine! I started using Keurig at my job and that\'s where I learned how easy it is. It was on sale for Christmas so decided this would be my gift to myself. I read through the instructions and it was very easy to setup and brew for the first time. I haven\'t had to clean it yet so I can\'t speak on that. So far, great results!!'),
(9210, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-16', 'Awesome Great, cant ask for any better'),
(9211, 14, 2, 4, '2015-12-11', 'Great product Great product! Excellent for juices, cakes'),
(9212, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-22', 'This is amazing I really like the keurig 200. It\'s my first one I have ever bought and I absolutely love it.'),
(9213, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Great model, great quality, great price My husband and I chose a Keurig to replace our traditional coffee maker. We couldn\'t have chosen a better model to suit our needs. We did quite a bit of shopping around, comparing prices and features of a lot of different models. This one is large but compact, the tank is large, and it couldn\'t be more easy or user-friendly. My husband and I only drink one cup a day on average, so this was the perfect alternative to wasting most of a pot of coffee. You will love the on-screen controls and all the options available to customize your brew. Cleaning is a breeze. This was a perfect transition for us, and I would definitely recommend this model to anyone looking to upgrade from a traditional coffee maker, or from a smaller Keurig system.'),
(9214, 13, 2, 3, '2015-06-10', 'Like the size of it - not so bulky This is in our breakroom and used daily. I don\'t like the idea it won\'t shutoff unless I unplug it. It has the power button on the screen but will turn on but not off. Is this how it work or is this defective? The water gets warm in the back. I have had many other Keurig machines and love them.'),
(9215, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-11', 'Makes good tasting coffee This unit is fast and makes very good tasting coffee. Works great at night when you just want one cup. Thanks, Keurig for the free pods for the review.'),
(9216, 13, 2, 2, '2015-10-21', 'Shut off This machine does not have an automatic on/off feature. I called support and they said it goes to \"sleep\" but machine was still warm 8 hrs later. Coffee is Lukewarm when brewed.'),
(9217, 13, 2, 5, '2016-10-22', 'Keurig 250 plus I brought this yesterday in the new color \"Oasis\". I\'m very happy with it and the color fits right into my Florida kitchen. This is my first Keurig and I\'m sure it won\'t be the last. The large reservoir was the reason I chose this model.'),
(9218, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-07', 'absolutely LOVE this brewing system! I love this brewing system! It\'s super convinent, fast, user friendly and has many cup size settings which I love! I love the strong brew feature as well! It also has a water filter that comes with it! amazing!'),
(9219, 13, 2, 4, '2015-05-04', 'Impressed I recently had a baby, so you can image how happy I was when the Keurig 2.0 joined my small kitchen appliances. It makes brewing/cleaning so much easier AND I can use it one-handed (since my baby is almost always in the other one). I just ordered the Keurig My K-Cup Reusable Coffee Filter so that I can also brew coffee from my local artisan roasters - I\'m excited about that!'),
(9220, 13, 2, 5, '2015-12-30', 'great coffee maker awesome machine'),
(9221, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-24', 'New to Keurig I am new to the Keurig family and love this machine! It\'s super easy, fast, and I love that it has a \"strength\" control, as I love a good strong cup of coffee in the morning. I love the variety of having coffee, tea, hot chocolate... and that I can make a cup or a carafe. Over all I am very pleased.'),
(9222, 13, 2, 4, '2015-07-20', 'Love it!! we purchased a Keurig after vacationing in NYC where our hotel had an in room Keuring coffee maker. We enjoyed the hot coffee in the morning and evening. I like to have a cup at night after dinner. This coffee maker works perfect for the one cup scernio and it makes great coffee. No messing with grinding coffee beans and using filters. Just pop in the pod and you have a great cup of coffee. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(9223, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-14', 'Great Brewer ! I enjoy multiple cups of coffee every day. I am the only person in my home that drinks coffee so I love that I can brew just one cup at a time. I also love that you an select to make it a strong cup of coffee. It heats up and is very quick so it is very convenient . I would recommend this product to anyone I know! This brewer is a coffee lovers dream come true.'),
(9224, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-13', 'Love my Coffee! I really enjoyed the 2.0. I like that you can change the cup size, quick to turn on & easy to brew. The design is sleeker than past versions & looks great on my counter! I do wish the reservoir was bigger, that would be the only thing I would maybe change.'),
(9225, 14, 2, 1, '2015-12-10', 'Got the used item Item had stains of food on it'),
(9226, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-23', 'Lots to Love! This little machine has lots to love! It\'s compact size makes it perfect for small kitchens and travel, and it is much quieter than our other 2.0 machine! It is fast and hot, and we\'ve been loving it! Pros: quiet, efficient, small footprint, cute colors, hot water setting (no more holding down the brew button for it to spit out a tiny amount of hot water, it now has a setting for it when you close the top with no K-cup in it!), comes with descaling solution and water filters. Cons: water reservoir is on the back of the machine, making it hard to access if it\'s under an upper cabinet in the kitchen, there\'s no auto-off function Overall, we\'re really happy that we were given the machine to test out and review, and have been using it multiple times every day!'),
(9227, 14, 2, 1, '2015-04-28', 'Would Not Recommend This Blender Motor burned out while liquefying soft avocados. I had it less than a year and only used it about 15 times. Very disappointed.'),
(9228, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-15', 'Loving my coffee all day This is a great step up from the original Keurig I had. I can now brew my coffee either by the cup, travel mug, or carafe. True this model doesn\'t come with a carafe, but for the price it\'s well worth it. With this being an entry level Keurig 2.0 if you add a carafe to it the price is still lower than the other Keurig 2.0 models. It also has a touchscreen with several options to choose from with each cup or carafe of coffee brewed. This is a more compact model compared to my other Keurig so I can save more counter space in the kitchen for other things. This particular model of Keurig I had received as a gift. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9229, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Love my new Keurig! I use this about 2/3 times per week and its perfect - fast and easy to use, plus the turquoise color really makes a nice pop of color in the kitchen. My only complaint is that a regular sized Tervis cup barely fits underneath, it could be about 1cm taller. Other then that I love it! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review!'),
(9230, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-26', 'GOOOD THING IT WAS A GIFT Like the speed at which a cup is brewed....not the time it takes waiting for pre-heat....only to wind up with a small, tepid cup of coffee....If you\'re a milk user, have a microwave closeby....better yet, stick to instant or a drip coffee maker.'),
(9231, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-08', 'Keurig I bought the tiffany blue color and not only am I absolutely in love with the color.. I love the convenience of the Keurig!'),
(9232, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-14', 'Keurig K200 I have been using this coffee maker for one week and it is nice.  We love the narrow design as compared to the wide-body Keurig we used before.'),
(9233, 13, 2, 4, '2016-05-02', 'K200 2.0 Brewer finally delivers!!! Ok, so this is a saga..bear with me. It started in September when I ordered the \"old\" Keurig system, because I had heard too many negatives about the 2.0. Well, the old one, a K45, didn\'t work well at all. I complained and Keurig sent the K2.0 350 as a replacement. No better! They sent out a K2.0 300. It was the same. Took way over 2 minutes to brew a cup. In the meantime, as I am complaining to family and friends about the lengthy brew time, they informed me, three of them, that the K2.0 200 worked like a charm and delivered coffee quickly! As I called again about the horrible performance of the K2.0 300, Keurig graciously offered to upgrade to the more expensive model. I immediately said \"No, just send me the cheaper one, the K2.0 200, because I know this one has a good track record.\" This model works the best! Believe me!!! Fast brewing (50 seconds), hot, and you can use your own coffee pod to brew your own brand without using the expensive Kcups, if that is what you want to do!! It took me 4 Keurigs to finally get one that delivers. This one is finally a keeper!!!'),
(9234, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-22', 'Wonderful and convienent brewer My family uses this product everyday, it is very fast and convenient. With 3-4 people using this brewer daily the water supply held in the brewer needs to be refilled after about 2 cups, which becomes tedious. On the up side, the water holder is located behind the brewer and is a great space savor. I love this product, but I would not recommend it for families of more than 2 or 3. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9235, 13, 2, 1, '2015-09-14', 'Broke after two weeks of getting it...twice!!!! So I waited for along time to get a Keurig, finally I got one of the k200 2.0 brewers loved it at first but after about two weeks it stopped working all together. So I took it back and got a new one giving them another chance same model and everything, it worked great for about two weeks and then just stopped working again! I can\"t believe that it happened twice in a row this time I just took it back and got my money back I don\'t know if I will purchase another one ever again!'),
(9236, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-18', 'Classic look in black & silver! I shied away from purchasing Keurig brewers for several years. It seemed an expensive way to brew coffee, but if one looks at the major coffee shops, this is a a lot more cost efficient per cup. In the last 6 months not only have I purchased the 2.0 which is compact which is what I was looking for, but also the Rivo unit. The 2.0 makes a very good cup of coffee in multiple sizes, as well as tea, and hot cocoa. The ease of use makes it very accessible for each of my family members! \"Thanks, Keurig , for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(9237, 13, 2, 5, '2016-11-26', 'Love I love the color and the machine.'),
(9238, 13, 2, 1, '2016-12-07', 'Mom\'s Christmas present I ordered this for my Mom for Christmas.  I paid $4.99 for gift wrapping,  Of course, the package gets delivered NOT wrapped and in the visible Keurig box!!  Great job Target!!'),
(9239, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-03', 'Nice Love it great quality'),
(9240, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Yummmm! Got it for my boyfriend for Christmas. We\'re both enjoying it :)'),
(9241, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-30', 'Great coffee maker!! Brew hot cocoa\'s and coffee\'s beautifully! every time I was looking for reviews I was turned off at the whole \"monopoly\"on the old K-cups not working. I literally busted out my crafting razor and cut off the top of a newer K-cup and attached it to the old k-cup... whalla coffee from an older k-cup. Honestly its not that big of a deal!!!! I would definitely recommended this brewer!'),
(9242, 13, 2, 5, '2016-03-04', 'no lead Being worried about the threat of lead in the machine, I had the water that flowed through the Keurig tested at National Testing Labs. The results found no lead in the water samples that I sent. Now I can use the machine with no worries about it!'),
(9243, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-04', 'Best Coffee Maker Ever I love to use this Keurig coffee maker. It is my first one to own, and I do not think I will be able to get another one after this. It was kind of complicated to originally set up, but after that, it became very easy to make a cup of coffee. LOVE IT. Thanks Keurig for the free pods for this review.'),
(9244, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-14', 'Overall a great product I love my morning cup of coffee. I wake up looking forward to it every morning. When I received my Keurig 2.0 from Influenster to review, I was elated. It is so convenient to brew one cup at a time. I was used to using a conventional brewer and always guessing just how much water to put in for my one lonely cup, now my Keurig does the measuring for me. And if I decide I need a second cup to cure my afternoon crash, it\'s not a problem. I only wish my travel mug fit under so I could brew and run out to enjoy my coffee in the car loop. I also love that it despenses hot water for an evening cup of tea or to make the kids hot cocoa. One thing missing is an auto shut off. It would be nice if it turned it self off after a certain amount of time.'),
(9245, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-29', 'Love!! Awesome product my husband and I love it! We got the teal and it\'s gorgeous'),
(9246, 14, 2, 1, '2015-02-27', 'Not a good product Got this for a wedding present, tried to make smoothies with it, barely even blended frozen fruits and yogurt. Left pretty big chunks, and would have to stir it every 5 seconds because it would freeze up. After five uses, it quit working completely. Only had it for one year, and used it five times.'),
(9247, 13, 2, 4, '2015-10-31', 'I can\'t imagine coffee making life without it Love it, so convenient, easy to clean! The only thing is after some time the water does not flow as much so you find yourself using the higher settings to get a medium sized cup. Other than that it\'s awesome highly recommended. Thank you Keurig for the free pots for this review.'),
(9248, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-30', 'First Time Keurig Owner My Husband and I have had a regular coffee maker since we got married almost 3 years ago. I have been trying to get him to let us get a Keurig because we have very different taste in coffee. I will defiantly not go back to a regular coffee pot, this has made our mornings so much easier!'),
(9249, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-09', 'Fianc loved the color Fianc loved the color'),
(9250, 13, 2, 4, '2016-10-08', 'Simple & easy to use After 4-1/2 years, my first Keurig stopped working.  I love the coffee maker!  Now I have a new love.   My Keurig K250 is very easy to use and doesn\'t take up a lot of room on my counter.  The only drawback is I\'m unable to use my re-useable cups with this machine.  So I can\'t brew my favorite coffee.  I will have to purchase a different cup in order to do that. :('),
(9251, 13, 2, 1, '2015-12-27', 'disappointed It takes a lot to get me upset in the morning when I wake up. So imagine how upset I was when I could not make my first cup of coffee of the day ! I love the Keurig brand, but I love my coffee more. And this new 2.0 is not compatible with my reusable filter ! So i had to disconnect the new 2.0 and put in my old Keurig Elite B45 Brewer which accepts all types of reusable filters. I am on a fixed income and cannot afford to buy a specific filter or buy the Keurig brand K-cups. so most likely I will return this 2.0 ! As I stated before I love my coffee more than a machine to make it !!! Yes I like the touch screen and yes I like the compact design. I also like the fact that I can add a carafe as well and I am upset that I will not be able to enjoy these amenities ! I was really excited and was brimming with anticipation to use this Keurig 2.0 K200 ! And now with one issue(reusable filter),my hopes were shattered, and my morning ruined ! Thanks Keurig !'),
(9252, 13, 2, 1, '2016-06-15', 'Coffee tastes bad Unlike some of the other reviewers,  I wasn\'t paid with free Keurig coffee to write a positive review.  I\'ve had this coffeemaker for a few months and the coffee tastes like plastic. I have done everything they said to do to get rid of it, but it is still there.   It doesn\'t get the coffee hot enough.   You have to use the new kcups with DRM technology or try one of the hacks you can find online. A few times it has left coffe grounds in the bottom of my cup.'),
(9253, 13, 2, 4, '2017-01-17', 'This is a great Keurig, easy to use and quick to get that cup of coffee!'),
(9254, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-02', 'Sleek and stylish with good coffee we finally upgraded from the Origional keurig that we\'ve had for over 5 years and so happy we did! Love the new design, saves so much space! Has options for how many oz. you want, including sizes that fill up a coffee thermos.  It warms up quick and is quiet. Also comes with a filter so you no longer need to clean it out every couple months with vinegar. Love the red color we ordered as well!'),
(9255, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-29', 'Keurig 2.0 250 This is the 2nd Keurig Machine that I have owned and will be the last. Not only am I beyond frustrated, I purchased the machine only to get it home and found that it had been previously purchased and used (and broke and returned the store with a used K cup still in it GROSS) I then came back home and unpacked a new machine and had problems with that one, and called Kurig customer service only to be treated rudely. This machine does not read the top of the K cups nor does the outside of the packaging indicate that you CAN\'T use your old K cups with it. So folks if you don\'t have the right K cups - beware, you will have to go out and purchase the right ones to use with this machine. Then, hold your breath that the machine will hold the water and it won\'t leak all over the place. Horrible experience with this thing!!!'),
(9256, 13, 2, 4, '2015-04-24', 'Great! Perfect for a new mommy!'),
(9257, 13, 2, 5, '2016-02-19', 'I LOVE my Keurig 2.0 K200 I am a late bloomer as a coffee drinker and only drink \"specialty\" type drinks. Took me 5 years trying to talk myself into buying a Keurig. I finally did it last October. WoW...am I ever glad I dd. I use it for hot coffee drinks, iced tea (brewed with hot water), cocoa, soups, instant hot cereals. I have just ordered another one to put into my RV when we set it up as a home away from home. It is WoNdErFuL!!! The only thing that is bother is that I run my water through a Britta before putting it into the Keurig. Probably overdoing it...but I haven\'t had any problems for 4 months of constant use.'),
(9258, 13, 2, 4, '2015-06-20', 'Disappointed at 10 oz. maximum.... Seems like it just fills half the cup, 12oz. Maximum would have made a big difference'),
(9259, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-21', 'love it! Best coffee maker I have yet to buy!'),
(9260, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-27', 'Great Coffee Without the Hassle As a Keurig virgin, this unit was easy to set up is highly flexible and the colour makes it stand out from the crowd. A real Gem!'),
(9261, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'keurig out of box - add water - ready to use'),
(9262, 13, 2, 5, '2015-11-20', 'Great coffee maker!!! Love it! Excellent product and Keurig\'s customer service is unmatched! I will recommend this product to everyone I know!'),
(9263, 13, 2, 1, '2016-03-28', 'Coffee grounds, error messages This is our third Keurig in as many years. This one became problematic shortly after we bought it. The bottoms of the coffee cups are COVERED with coffee grounds, error messages come on intermittently, and the water is not hot enough. My husband has spoken with people at Keurig and done everything they have suggested...to no avail. We\'re looking into buying a different brand next time....'),
(9264, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-03', 'I love this Keurig! I love this Keurig! Great technology upgrade from the mini Keurig. I do, however, wish I would have purchased the larger model that holds more water and comes with a carafe. Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.'),
(9265, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Best deal Great coffee maker and got such a great deal'),
(9266, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-12', 'Great Product!! Thanks Keurig, for the free pods for this review! I use this product every day! The screen lights up wonderfully so I am able to see what size cup I am brewing without having to turn on a light.'),
(9267, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-11', 'Perfect Delayed shipment but worth the wait. Love the oasis color. Keurig has implemented an infrared ink sensor with this model only permitting Keurig brand K-cups to be used. Research the 2.0 K-cup restrictions for any easy solution to use universal k-cups.'),
(9268, 13, 2, 4, '2015-09-17', 'Wild about Keurig The newer brewer are more rickety than the older models, but still work well. I\'ve purchased as gifts for 4 other family members & they all love them & use them daily.'),
(9269, 13, 2, 5, '2017-01-01', 'Extremely Pleased! I like the versatility of the mug and carafe size options and the sleeker look.'),
(9270, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-11', 'Attractive addition to the counter. Was looking for a light-colored Keurig with carafe and this will do nicely. I do wish the temperature was hotter but I know that\'s a safety issue. I recommend shoppers make sure of the distance between countertop and bottom of upper cabinets. Users will most likely have to pull it forward on the counter to gain the vertical space needed to open the top  and insert a pod, and it\'s awkward to do if there is water in it.'),
(9271, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-23', 'Still Love My Keurig After having a previous Keurig for 5 years (and it still works!) we decided to upgrade to this one to be able to make pots/carafes of coffee also. I love this new option! However you will need to buy the carafe and different size kcup OR the reusable carafe size coffee filter. The color is awesome and looks really neat in my kitchen. The only thing I have noticed different is that you must use KEURIG brand k cups because it detects the lid in order to brew it perfectly (hot chocolate differs from coffee for example). When I looked at my stash of Keurig kcups I realized everyone I own is Keurig brand anyway, so it was not a deal breaker for me. Keurig has TONS of brands associated with them.'),
(9272, 13, 2, 5, '2015-05-29', 'Great Product! Effective, Efficient and Stylish This Keurig is a great deal for the money! I use it every day, and have been pleasantly surprised each time. The large water reservoir and touchscreen make this product even more convenient and set it apart from the last generation of Keurig brewers. Definitely try one out, as it is well worth the money.'),
(9273, 13, 2, 4, '2016-12-16', 'Keurig coffee maker So easy to use and fun, lots of flavor choices. Cheaper than buying special coffees out but more expensive than a regular coffee maker.'),
(9274, 13, 2, 5, '2016-11-30', 'My first Keurig I love my new Keurig! Have been looking at them for months but undecided whether to buy one. Went to my brother\'s house who has one and loved how fast I could have a fresh cup of coffee. Then when I saw it in the Oasis color I had to get it. It matches my beachy kitchen decor perfectly. The coffee tastes great and it\'s simple to use. Now I just have to find the pods for the carafe.'),
(9275, 14, 2, 5, '2014-11-02', 'A Great Blender My sister loves it. Her grandchildren shouted Smoothies as soon as they saw it. It\'s multi-purpose so the whole family can use and enjoy it.'),
(9276, 13, 2, 5, '2015-06-01', 'Love it! we love this product! We brew coffee every morning using out 12 cup regular brewer however, we love the option of having a cup of coffee whenever we want without the hassle of having to brew a whole pot. We love our Keurig for that reason.'),
(9277, 13, 2, 4, '2015-08-17', 'Makes Good coffee but use Starbucks Pods Really like my Keurig being that its the first one I\'ve owned. I would however recommend purchasing the Starbuck brand K cups. Coffee is almost as strong like at the coffee shop. \"Thanks, Keurig, for the free pods for this review.\"'),
(9278, 13, 2, 2, '2016-08-16', 'New K250: havoc on carafe options I am disappointed that Keurig has made changes to prevent the carafe settings from working...with a carafe! with a K-carafe or My K-Cup Hot!!!  I feel like I\'ve wasted $140 (machine + carafe) and can\'t use what the product was advertised to do.   (I\'d upload a pic, but this website won\'t let me.)'),
(9279, 13, 2, 2, '2017-01-08', 'Stick to the old one The new K Hot looks sleek, slim and modern on my marble counter tops but it can\'t beat the love I had for my original Keurig. The new K Hot does NOT allow programmable on/off times (like the original one). It only allows Keurig brand coffee pods. No more Target brand coffee~ It does not display the time of day. Overrated. Stick to the original Keurig machine. Wish I still had mine.'),
(9280, 13, 2, 5, '2015-08-11', 'Love it! We love that we don\'t have to both drink the same coffee. Unit is very easy to use. We bought the Keurig to replace another brands single serve that was awful.'),
(9281, 13, 2, 1, '2017-01-19', 'Great idea, poor quality I have had a version of a Keurig for the better part of the last 10 years. My current model, the Cuisinart SS-700, is quite a few years old, and I was growing tired of having a separate coffee pot for when we have company. I thought this would be the answer to my prayers!  WRONG. This version is so loud. At first I thought maybe I had received a bad model so I watched some YouTube videos and heard the same noise. The pump sounds like it\'s taking in water in glugs, and having a hard time doing it. Nothing like either of my old Keurigs. This particular model isn\'t programable, so if you liked/wanted that feature, you would need to upgrade to one of the two higher models.  I will say that this model is slimmer in width than the older models which is still a plus. And if you can get past the noise, it would give the opportunity to make a carafe or a single serving.  I am glad I only ran water through it a few times because this is going back to the store tomorrow.'),
(9282, 13, 2, 4, '2016-02-15', 'Love it except for 1 problem Great coffee, but with the electric rates around here, I wish there was an auto on/off option'),
(9283, 13, 2, 5, '2015-07-16', 'Life changing If you have problems with arthritis in your hands, this is for you. My morning cup of tea is less painful, this was made with me in mind.'),
(9284, 13, 2, 5, '2015-04-27', 'Why Did I Wait So Long We have had a simple coffee maker since we got married 2 years ago! I never wanted wanted to spend the money on \"just a coffee maker\" but we finally tried the Keurig and it is awesome! We love the ease of use and how quickly it can brew up! You can make an individual cup or if you buy the carafe(you can make enough for the group) I love the versatility of all the flavors as well! My husband is a coffee drinker and I am a tea drinker So this works out nicely! I even make our breakfast oatmeal with it! Makes mornings a breeze in our house! We won\'t be going back to a normal coffee maker anytime soon!'),
(9285, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-27', 'Awesome purchase Love Keurig and ease of useing..'),
(9286, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-31', 'Love it!! I love my new Keurig it is so easy to use and so practical!'),
(9287, 13, 2, 1, '2016-01-24', 'K250 Stopped Measuring water correctly I have an older Keurig that has worked perfectly for several years. Decided to purchase K 2.0 250. It worked for about 30 days. Now it doesn\'t measure water correctly, sometimes it brews continuously until manually cancelled. No longer a dependable coffee maker.... Switching back to older model.'),
(9288, 13, 2, 5, '2016-12-26', 'Wonderful! The purple color is beautiful and the price was great!');
